Welcome back to The Elder Scrolls Online! Here are some of the things you might have missed since your last login:nn Armor Dyes: Visit a Dye Station in any major city to customize the coloration of your armor. Unlock new dyes by completing achievements!n New Veteran Dungeons: Return to conquered dungeons and experience the continued story of those locations!n Craglorn: The first adventure zone is available! Venture to Craglorn and unravel the secrets of the Celestials, do battle with monstrous foes, and challenge the malevolent Serpent!n Trials: Confront the Celestial Warrior, the Celestial Mage, and the Celestial Serpent in our 12-player Trials! Available in two difficulty modes.n Dragonstar Arena: You and three friends can enter the Dragonstar Arena, a brand new four player challenge for veteran rank players. Are you mighty enough to defeat all comers?"n Guild Heraldry: Show your guild pride by donning a customized tabard available in the guild store.n Improved Guild Functionality: Create, remove, and assign more granular permissions to individual guild ranks.n New Facial Animations! Characters in the world will now speak more naturally and animate appropriately.n Crafting Writs and Certification! Visit a major city in your alliance to embark on the path to certification.n Countless bug fixesn Increased security against bots and spamn Improvements to multiplayer activity in overworld areasn Improved combat responsiveness in high-stress situations

I cannot get Pierric's disappearance off my mind.  He was like a younger brother to me.
You know, the truth is that this was partially my fault for leading Julien on in the first place. I knew he wasn't the one. I won't torture that poor boy any longer.
You are not one of my usual customers, stranger.
Ah, the good samaritan returns.  What can I do for you?
Who are you, and what are you doing in Crosswych? Better not stir up any trouble or I'll take you out myself.
Thank you for helping me. Guendeline is so beautiful! And the necklace. It really brings out the color of her eyes.nnI can't wait to tell Mother all about this!
Whew! That was a close one!
Any luck in finding the poisoner of my precious land?
I can't believe Tarrant actually suspected me.  Thank you for clearing up that misunderstanding, friend.
Have you discovered the fate of my courier?
Aubrey's productivity has trebled since Julien entered her life. I think I have you to thank for that, friend.
We don't serve strangers here.  Speak to the Warden, then we can talk - not before.
Not sure what you're doing out on the moors, but we can't take any chances.  Leave our camp, immediately!
If you don't get the 'all clear' from the Warden, I'll not be speaking to you.
Finally, I can sleep through the mornings. Thank you!
I hope you're happy. Brought the fox right into the henhouse, didn't you?
Help Oron unravel this mystery. I rely now on both of you. Time is running out. Make haste!
Who knows how many other villagers are actually werewolves?
You did all you could. Eagle's Watch... will survive.
How's the collection coming? Those zombies aren't getting any younger.
So. I guess the fact that we killed a necromancer together means we have to be friends now. Hmph.
You'd best not be here to cause trouble, or the Watch will make quick work of you. Speak to Warden Godwin if you're going to be sticking around.
In Ulorion's Name, tis good to see another Watcher out here.
I suppose you've heard what the villagers have to say about me. What will you do about it?
You have shown great courage and kindness. My sisters and I thank you.
What news of Morgan Frey?
Jacinta's remedy is almost complete. Did you bring my poison sample?
Are you looking into that lake problem for me?
You know, Old Scar isn't going to up and kill hisself.
You are an invaluable ally to the Hands. We are lucky to have you here, and the citizens of Camlorn thank you.
You've been a great help. Remind me that once the city is quiet again, I owe you a drink.
Have you slain Vorgo yet?  With every day that passes, another innocent is burgled or slain...
How goes the salvage? They giving you trouble?
You've bled for the line. My men and I thank you.
I still need those symbols to prevent these soldiers from being risen against us later.
Your kindness reminds me that there is light at the end of the tunnel. Thank you for your help. Maybe one day when this is all over, we can share a drink.
So the necromancer is dead. Your efforts may have saved us all, friend.
Even the truly pious can be corrupted. Take care you remain with the just, friend.
You and I, we did a great thing for Northmoor. If you ever need a ready sword, call on me.
You look like you're looking for something... or someone. These eyes see everything in town, from way up here...
I'll be perfectly fine. Fear not.
Thank you so much for taking care of those bears.
Elsie's plotting her revenge on all those who went with Roche. I reckon one of those was you, eh?
We've got fresh water again! I don't care what people say about you. You're all right in my book.
Hey! It's the savior of the bar! Old Varle over there has started serving again. Good thing, too. I was having trouble explaining to my wife why I'm always here.
I can't believe you'd go against Elsie with Roche. Get out of my sight!
Were the undead removed? I'm glad I could help.
I appreciate you checking on me. I'm glad to have been able to help you with the undead. These bandits don't concern me nearly as much.
It's good to see you well. We have not forgotten what you did for us.
I guess I can find some real friends... you're nice!
I'll be all right, now... thanks to you.
I am in your debt, friend.  What can I do for you?
Thanks to you, we may soon be able to retake the docks. You have my eternal gratitude.
Believe me when I tell you, Arnand will help you - although he may require that you help him first...
Any luck finding my chest? My livelihood depends upon it!
We're going to be a family again. I'm so happy.
Well. At least my mushrooms are safe, now.
We'll see to the children. I promise. Thank you for all your help.
GiNGEr break cooked fhjahfahj
We must discover where that scampering courier hid the weapon.

Praise the Divines, you bring great news! The cultists, dead. Namira's servant, destroyed. Such feats demand reward. Speak to our supply officer, Bruno Dabney. We have gathered powerful artifacts to fight evil. You may have your pick of them.
You would make a fine addition to the Magis Order. Fight well and smite evil.
Have you news of Ranser's murder?
The Adamant Crown has cracked, and war will come of it, mark my words!
Is there something I can do for you?
I trust you will prove Sebastian's innocence.
Look in the house on the edge of town for Jacinta - you'll see some Wyrd witches outside.
So nice to see you again.
Thank you again, friend.
I hate this place.
<Gargast is no longer here. He is conditionally invisible.>
I must remain here. Without my power, the Countess will expire.
I cannot leave the Countess's side.
Keep that soulstone safe. I'll want it back.
Is Necanis dead?
Thanks for helping me out. I'm gonna rest easier knowing those wolves got what was coming to 'em.
Have you returned with the herbs? I cannot express how grateful I am for your help.
New to Camlorn? I haven't seen you around.
Be wary of the Order if you're out and about.
Have you read this so-called "Hands of Northmoor" propaganda? Disgraceful.
I appreciate your help with these spirits. I've worried about handling them alone.
Have you read this so-called "Hands of Northmoor" propaganda? Disgraceful.
Greetings, child. How may this disciple of Zenithar help you profit?
Thank you for delivering my shipment to Wayrest... Didn't want Iamel sending his cronies after me!
You look like trouble. I won't involve myself with you until you speak to the Warden
An assassin? Our task is more pressing than I'd realized. Catch your breath, and then tell me when you are ready for us to move on.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
You'd do well to join the Order. They could use someone like you.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
You look like trouble. I won't involve myself with you until you speak to the Warden.
Don't think I'll forget you sided with Roche. I've got nothing else to say to you.
Once we have reclaimed our tree, I will have the strength to heal Varic. After you've cleansed the Wyrd Tree of its evil spirit, my sisters and I will meet you there.
Were you able to find our things?
You've saved us all! We cannot thank you enough, sir.
My family can't be far... please friend, hurry and find them.
Courageous and powerful. You laugh in the face of the undead. Who ARE you?
Kill me or save her, hero.  What will it be?
You're handy in a fight, my friend!
<Patroller Wayle moans in pain.>
Thanks for your help. The healers should be here soon, yes?
We'll clean up here. Go tell Lady Kallath that we found Dalomar's killers.
Thanks for the help. Kallath will want to speak with you.
Divines watch over you, friend.
What happened?  You... you pulled me from that horror.  Thank you!
Sincerely, you have my thanks. Please see Warden Godwin. I've sent word ahead.
What news of Morgan Frey?
I'm never traveling again! Oh, brave knight, thank you once more for your kindness.
Gods speed you! Be wary of dangers on the road.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
You look like trouble. I won't involve myself with you until you speak to the Warden.
You look like trouble. I won't involve myself with you until you speak to the Warden.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
Please, these men still live, but not I fear for long...
Hello, traveler.
Hello again! Have you found enough Drythistle yet?
I'm not letting Grit out of my sight again. Thanks!
I think I can calm down the rest of them. I'm sure you have other work to do. Thank you for your help.
That beast would have surely killed me. I don't know what's happening, where things went wrong.nnWilliam's gone mad! Please, you must talk to him. You must save him!
We haven't much time. Even now I sense the approach of the Coldun legion. We will make our final stand within the town of Alaygon.
Always an exhilarating experience going into the Spirit Realm like that. You fought well!
From the moment I saw you, I knew you could complete the task at hand. Now it is our time to aid you against that of flesh and steel.
You're... alive? I.. I am sorry I doubted you, stranger. You have proven me wrong and for that I apologize. My sister appears to have been right.
Is so much better now that wolfies is all transmorphed!
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
If you're here to cause trouble, the Watch will run you through.
Stay back! There's an injured man here!
Fantastic! You are a true hero. My Emeric will never believe the stories I have for him, now.
Amazing. You need no affiliation or justification for doing good. You are an inspiration to my men and I. Camlorn is safe because of you.
Return to me when you've completed my task.
You say you destroyed the wraiths? That's great news! Now if I can just get Danain to pay me...
I'm so scared.. what do I do? What do I do?
I miss my father.. but I know he will be safe when Coldun attacks. At least I can give myself that assurance.
Quickly now, speak to Scag. You do not have much time.
Guess we helps you, since you kind of helps us!
You have risked your life for a simple town that you do not call home. I owe it to you to at least know the truth of it all.
These Bloody Eyes weird. Something about protecting veal? Why you protect food?
Hah! You see them runs away from me?
We dids it! Doogie sleep well now I think.. thanks much to you!
You've done us all a great favor, friend. Please, speak to Tamarus. I believe it is time he told you the truth.
You fought well. You should join us, as one of our guard!
The battle of the flesh realm has been won for this day, yet the battle within the Veil will always continue.
Since I lost my brother within the Veil, I've searched for purpose.. but today I found it. Thank you, stranger.
Keep away from me, stranger.
The jokes are free and the services reasonably priced!
Who am I to interfere with a person who speaks to Kings. How very impressive. Where to?
Welcome back. Where would you like to go?
What can I interest you in, hm?
Yes, may I help you?
Work, work, work! Haven't seen my wife in so long, she'll forget what I look like.
Have you made up your mind to help us?
Are you ready to do the right thing and help the Hands?
Dark times are upon us. Wolves, spiders, disease...what have we done to anger Y'ffre?
We're each doing the work of three men now and I'm barely able to stand. Go bother someone else!
The wolves get so close; I can feel their breath in my sleep...if I got any sleep, that is.
Can't get but a moment's rest! If it's chatter you want, see the Foreman up at the camp.
I don't think we're safe yet
Stay safe out there.
Leave me be! I'm off, already!
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
Have you retrieved my valuables? Quit dawdling and get on it!
Business is good - I can trade with Grayborne again. Thank you, friend!
I will handle any remaining spirits in Camlorn. Make haste to the Redoubt. I fear our attacker has far darker plans than it first appeared.
Muahahaha!
It is unfair, I know, but whenever I see you now I fear you bring bad tidings...
I trust you will prove Sebastian's innocence.
Leave me be! I'm off, already!
<The bloated body of this man is weighted down with rocks. He wears the uniform of a Hands of Northmoor Orator.>
Good day again. You've not decided to become a lumberjack now, have you?
Your help means so much to me.
The disappearance of Ranser's body has caused quite a stir, one I must settle. When I've settled things in Camlorn, I'll join you in Grayborne. Hurry now to Constable Brennoc in Grayborne.
Your aura is diminished, though there is great power in it. nnI can heal your soul, if you so desire.
Man, it was awesome the way you killed all those goblins for me.
We are home at last. We will not leave again.
I wish I could help you further. I'm just... too scared.
Such power it had... yet you bested it. You are a true hero. Grayborne is saved.
Did you find my locket?
When you place their ashes into the fireplace of their old home, the Wyrd's spell will keep them safe forever.
Zoe sent you to me? Then I will certainly do whatever I can to help...
Achoo! Excuse me...these allergies are terrible!
This one is glad you will help Ailsa Baird in her last hours. Be safe.
All of Northmoor prays for your success, hero.
I have nothing more to say to you. Leave me to my misery.
We're each doing the work of three men now and I'm barely able to stand. Go bother someone else!
Now you know why we of the Ashen Order are called "Gravebinders". You're worthy of the name yourself.
The horrors of this place never cease. I urge you to leave, unless you can rouse an army to breach the keep and slay the dread Silvermist Queen.
Your face says it all. I'll never see my dear friend again. Tell me, has he been avenged?
What happened to <<1>> is a shame, but her sacrifice was not in vain.nn<<2>> is the only one who can hold Camlorn together.
How goes the cleansing?
Please check on Ahji at the Danain Family Tomb. The relic I sent her to look for may help us in our fight to retake Camlorn.
I remember you. You were going to help me, right?nnI need to go to Aldcroft, so I can report to Warden Rielle.
You're back, and little worse for wear. Is it done?
We can't let Faolchu's curse spread to Aldcroft. Do what you can to help Gloria. nnI trust your abilities.
You must find my sisters. Together, we are powerful. Alone, we will vanish.
There is much to be done and through my Familiar, I will guide you.
Be careful of those Bog Lurchers
If Angof knows what we know, then time is short. The safety of High Rock now falls on you.
You will find most of the hags around their huts to the west and north.nnWhen you fetch the hearts, bring them to us in our hut on the hill to the east.
Scattering my ashes on Elisa's grave will comfort me. Then I will know that some part of us rests together.
After what you did to stop General Faolchu, you're the only one I trust with this. nnHurry to Arnand. The fate of the kingdom may depend on you.
Is that wolf blood I see on you? I trust it's well earned.
After what you did to stop General Faolchu, you're the only one I trust with this. nnHurry to Arnand. The fate of the kingdom may depend on you.
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
I am honored to know you - I consider you as much a Gravebinder as any of my bretheren. But I fear the evil here is too much for us...
You see now what you oppose, Hero. You would not be blamed for turning away.
These roads should be safe, but they're not. nnKing Casimir is doing nothing to help us.
Those workers think they can laze about waiting for tools. Good thing you're putting an end to their idle behavior.
I'm surprised you dare show your face around here.  Go, before I make an example of you.
You've gathered the limbs? Wonderful. nnPlease take them to Wyress Ileana at the Dresan Ruins, northwest of here.
Your aid is appreciated. I gave protective charms to many of the wyresses, but I need you to deliver charms to three more.
Did you catch anything interesting?
Harpies eat sand fleas, you know. The sooner I get a harpy pet, the fewer sand fleas bites I'll have.
The spirits of the land are with you. Be safe on your journey.
I had hoped my sisters would survive this poison, but I fear there is little else I can do now. I can only comfort them until the end.
We've lost so much of Daenia's flora to corruption. I hope we can at least save the hawthorns.
I think we could both rest, knowing our granddaughter remembers us.
Don't worry. I'll be right along.
You're kind to come all this way, just to return a lost heirloom. I'll treasure it as a reminder of my grandparents.
The mistress is... watching you...
You've done what we could not. You've reclaimed the Wyrd Tree from its corruption.
So you've given tools to Pierre and Frizkav? I suppose we're the last group, then. Give them here.
Are Michelle and Pierre all right? These woods are not safe for anyone. What do you have there?
You've already spoken to Michelle and Frizkav? What do you want with me?
Your efforts have helped greatly. Be well.
The deputy you trained is already showing the others a thing or two. You did a fine job.
I am breath and life, wind and soul.
I am the oceans and the rain. I am the lifegiver.
All things come from me. All things return to me.
Please, take the ring to my brother. He's the warden right over there.
So you've gone out and risked life and limb, eh? My thanks to you, sincerely.
I realize I may have been rude earlier. You probably helped Zacharia's spirit rest a little easier when you killed Gog Dresan. I should thank you. nnThanks.
Well, you've certainly made Ormax happy by killing that big tree thing. nnI hear he might give us all a day off once a year, just to celebrate its death!
Good job with that Gog thing. That'll keep the lumber sailing... and the money flowing.
So you're our saviour? Really? nnPraise be to the Eight, but I think we're doomed.

By the Divines! I heard stories about you. They say you've killed the biggest of the big. nnDid you see my cousin while you were out there? He said he's killed bigger beasts than you have. nnDo you think he did? I bet he did. He's pretty strong.
I heard Bernard heard from Ormax that you killed that Gog Dresan thing. nnImagine that! I was the third person to hear about it! nnNonetheless, I must say: thank you, thank you, and thank you.
You don't know how happy I am to see the Spirits once again! Thank you for your work!
My sisters and I will honor this event in song for many ages.

We don't have many nice things handed down in our family, so I'm not worried about thieves. Still, it's sad to think someone would steal the Thierry's family heirloom. nnI hope someone catches that scoundrel soon.
We've heard stories of you from the foresters. Are you here to help us return home?

<It appears this merchant was freshly murdered by something from the swamp. Fresh trails of slime lead into the swamp to the east. It looks as if the crates he was carrying were dragged into the swamp...>
I've given you all the help I can. When we are done with the Alessians, I'll close the hole through which you came forever.
The Beldama Wyrd has heard of you, <<1>>.

More stew?  I'd think a hero such as yourself could eat a lot, though stew's not much good for carrying in your pockets.  Did you know my uncle Forton was an adventurer?  Well, he was something, let me tell you, had a bit of the Breton magic, he did.
What will you do, now that you know my part in this?
Thanks to your help, my job is made eaiser.
Ah! It's a shame you couldn't bring some spriggan bits for my fire. nnI like to watch them burn.
You're always welcome in my house. nnYou've done us a great service by killing that spriggan creature. I think we can handle the rest of them.
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
Who are you? Why are you pestering me?
My cousin is anxious to speak with you. I would not keep her waiting.
You have slept long, and well... and you have seen many things. Tell me all that you saw.
Good luck with the trappers - they're in that camp down the hill there, to the north.
Victory! Your deeds in Camlorn will not be forgotten.
Look who it is again! As I said, you can speak to Warden Moreau. He might offer you something if you mention his assistance in my endeavors. You'll find out what I mean.
That was a sight to behold. Varyllis is in your debt, Numinous.

Fortunately I have a flask prepared for just such a purpose. Within is a tonic that requires but a single reagent - a fresh Nimbleberry. The resulting concoction should remove the petrification effects on poor Ameralee.
Please speak to Battlereeve Heldarmo at the Verdant Grove Tower to the east.
Thank you again, Optimate. Have you returned to view our Imago Serries?
You have given Varyllis hope where little existed.
The longevity of a Numinous is only surpassed by their persistence. Here, take the Jewel and use it to slay the Maormer Scouts.
The Serries mirror our souls. Heed the insights Altmer art provides.
You may go ahead without me. I shall meet you in front of the Kinhouse.
I cannot see as I once did from beyond. Soon, I will pass from this plane entirely. Before I do, I hope to see you accomplish great things.
You defeated Faolchu! nnNow we can finally get those freeloaders from Camlorn out of our town.
Now that the wolves are gone, we can get rid of the Camlorn crowd. nnMaybe they'll take those pirate thugs with them.
Now that the werewolves have been defeated, the folks from Camlorn can return home. nnI do hope it's the end of their hardships, not the beginning.
With the wolves gone, those Camlorn folk can leave, and not a moment too soon.
Thank you for helping Camlorn. nnNow life around here can finally return to normal.
Faolchu is gone? Good. nnSoon I'll be able to go back to the pub again.
The Camlorn folk can return home? nnPerhaps I'll make my way up north and help them rebuild.
Foalchu dead? Things should be returning to normal around here soon, thank you.
The day's a little brighter now that Faolchu's gone.
I'm glad the werewolves are gone, but I don't know if I can ever go home.nnI can't go back, not after the horrors I saw there.
The wolves are gone? Thank goodness for that! nnStill, that's no excuse for the duke's inaction.
The wolves are gone! Now it's time to return and rebuild.
The wolves are gone! Now it's time to return and rebuild.
Ahnarra is ready to return to Camlorn. This one hopes all will be restored soon.
Camlorn is saved? I'm relieved, but I think I'll stay in Aldcroft.
Our triumph in Camlorn will be remembered for years to come.
You drove out Faolchu! I knew we would rid Camlorn of those damn wolves!
Those wolves were no match for us. nnHow did they even drive us out in the first place?
Camlorn is saved? Praise the Eight! nnI just hope we can restore the city to her former glory.
I can't wait to return home. Thank you for saving Camlorn.
The werewolves are gone? What do we do now? Rebuild? nnHow will we pay for it all?
With our victory in Camlorn, we can finally get out of this salty port town.
Victory! Soon Camlorn will be restored.
With the werewolves out of Camlorn, we can make our streets safe again.
Now that Camlorn is safe, I'll certainly stay here in Glenumbra.
Werewolves are no match for the Iron Circle!
Malauch was with us when we took the fight to the werewolves.
Now that Faolchu is dead, I really hope we can get out of this swamp. My boots haven't been dry since I got here.
Faolchu is dead? I'm kind of sad to be leaving. This place grows on you.
Faolchu was a real monster, but I'm more afraid of what we'll find north of here.
We did it! The sense of accomplishment can be a bit overwhelming.
So there really was an undead werewolf? nnWas he really as vicious as they said he was? nnWell, thanks to you, he won't trouble us again.
Camlorn is saved! nnDo we march north now?
What a fight! That werewolf won't be bothering anyone else.
Faolchu is dead. nnNow it's time to march north and put a stop to this madness once and for all.
Now that the fight with Faolchu is over, I can leave this tiny briny port.
We did a great deed here today. Now we can help Camlorn rebuild.
Faolchu is dead? nnI see another unpleasant sea voyage ahead of me.
Faolchu is dead! That's fantastic! Now we can finally get out of this swamp!
Now that Faolchu has fallen, maybe the Lion Guard will let me take some time to explore High Rock.
I do hope they can craft a Reverbelant - we must get that Varla Lens back!
You have blessed us, Numinous. No longer do Pallid Devils hurl rocks at us from Sunhold.
O mighty Serpent Slayer, the sea ebbs at your approach!
Optimate. Your efforts in Sunhold shall not go unrewarded.
All of Isque is in your debt, Numinous. I do not doubt your deeds will place you in the Kinlord's graces.
Oh, if only the wind would stop!
Magus Commander Danain knows what he's doing. We will retake Camlorn.
Could I risk leaving my soul gem for a day or two, the Orrery would be litered with dead Maormer.
We must finish the Blessed Bell as soon as possible. Your aid is required.
You must be quick to harvest the Discarnates before they cease to be a menace!
The pale cowards dare to plague the Orrery!
What match are werewolves for armor and magic?
Can't say I favor a fair fight, all out in the open like this. But the damned werewolves can smell us coming.
The Maormer plans are in disarray. You have done all I wished. Now I shall press them back into the sea!
The sooner you find those sheets the better.  Then I can put my efforts back into finding candied pheasant.
Healing can take many forms. We all know you're doing your best.
Well, I suppose we must chalk up that experience to experience, mustn't we?
My assistant believes that the thief can be tracked. She is crafting a device that will enable us to do so.
When you gave me Coren's locket I could feel his soul.nnDeath won't end our love. One day, beyond Aetherius, we'll be together again.
Talrien sent word of your task. Have you brought me the pieces of the crown?
Fivefold venerations, Optimate!
Worry not. I shall return to my daughter in the Kinhouse shortly.
Did you manage to land on the ships?
Though he was born in a humble village near Crosswych, my father became a captain in the Knights of the Dragon. I hope one day to rise to the same heights.
target: Though he was born in a humble village near Crosswych, my father became a captain in the Knights del Drago. I hope one day to rise to the same heights.

source: I can stop jumping everytime a Crosswych urchin comes to my door.  Thanks again for your help with Mother Murk!
I knew Arturo well! Sadly, you'll find nothing but his remains. nnLook for the leather necklace he always wore. His mother might like the memento. He fought the undead until the last.
Battlereeve Tariella can be found at the Harmonium fortress, along the coast south of the Isque Kinhouse.
Do not delay! Auri-El is primed for its return. Speak with Alorkhane, who waits near the Lover's shrine. She will instruct you further.
Those wolves were no match for us, how did they even drive us out in the first place?
You must not delay. Take Auri-El to High Kinlady Astraela in the Scintilla Kinhouse to the east.
Orgnavar's vile purpose is laid bare, thanks to your efforts. The Maormer are foul indeed to destroy the very skies with their evil schemes.
Had my students your foresight, the Orrery would not be in such disrepair.
None of these writings make sense.
Hurry to Magus Commander Panoit. I've done all I can for you here.
They tell me it is not my fault. Of course not. I just...  I just dropped a book. That's all.
Without you, we could not have possibly succeeded in stopping Angof... or his infernal benefactor, the Daedric Prince Molag Bal.nnThe kingdom owes you a debt of gratitude.
The Varla Lens is now in place, the lines of power restored. Your help was invaluable in this matter, <<1>>.
You have brought a cure? Free my body from this prison then, Numinous. Use the potion on my stone form, that I may return to myself.
Thank you for slaying that foul Pallid Devil witch. With her gone the Orrery will be a bit safer. Be sure to report to Vartisan Urselor in the Kinhouse.
Please hurry to the ruins. I would go myself, but I fear those spectres would be the end of me.
Did you find any other survivors? Is anyone down there still alive?
We won't forget your help, friend. Blessed arrows aren't easy to come by.
These people act as though they're the only ones who've suffered a loss. I came all this way to find out about Arturo. nnWhy won't any of the miners talk to me about him?
The Rogue Discarnates took my tools to the Maze of Obliquity to the north.
Beware the Blackhand Cultists. If they get in your way, do whatever is necessary. We must get the Midnight Talisman from Jadier!
Charascel...that's the lady that came barging in here, demanding things as though Crosswych isn't as good as Daggerfall. I don't know what happened to her son, but plenty of folk died in the mine.
Zhian did not know Arturo. Perhaps you should talk with Merard Alouette. Merard knew all the miners well.
At last, I can keep rats without those bloody chickens molesting them.
Many thanks for your aid in restoring the Felballin Varla Lens - as well as for saving me!
Were I you, I would not delay! The High Kinlady will not please herself to wait upon even one as accomplished as yourself.
Some miners told me about the help you gave them.  It's good to know we have real heroes among us now.
I've heard you've been helping the scholars at the ruins.nnDangerous business, I'd warrant.
I knew something was stirring up the undead. Even the guards were hearing tales about Angof!nnNow that he's gone, I'm sure the undead will return to their graves.
I'm sure the undead will return to their eternal rest, now that you've defeated Angof. nnSoon, we'll be able to relax our guard.
May you breathe freely forever. Go with my blessing.
May you never thirst. Go with my blessing.
May you always find shelter in the earth. Go with my blessing.
Scholar Lael never once told me I might have to explore the Dwynnarth Ruins. nnThat's not something I would do voluntarily.

The mine collapsed suddenly, and several miners were injured. Some went back in to find survivors.nnI'm worried. My parents died in a mine collapse, so I understand how painful it is to lose loved ones.
<<1>> has no doubts that that evil man will soon come up with another excuse to make <<1>>'s life miserable.
I appreciate the help, friend. All the same, you should keep your tales of what happened under your hat. nnWe really don't want to start another dispute.
Your perseverence and dedication to the improvement of our Menagerie is without peer. Hail to thee, Optimate!
Ah, the esteemed Kirin hunter. How fares your search?
So you've gone out and risked life and limb, eh? nnMy sincere thanks to you, friend.
Lately, several folks have noticed their possessions are missing.nnWe're not sure if it's a thieving ring or just plain forgetfulness, what with the spriggans about and all.
Thanks for helping with those damned spriggans. nnOrmax was happy to hear about it.
Apparently, killing those spriggans got Pierre to stop complaining. nnNow I've got twice as many reasons to thank you!
Spriggan Killer! I bet that's what they'll call you from now on. nnYou have our thanks.
Apparently killing those Spriggans even got Vincent to stop yapping on. Thank you!
Thanks to you, my job is now easier.
Thanks to you, my job is now eaiser.
Thanks to you, my job is now easier.
<<1>>, you really helped us out there. We should be receiving reinforcements from Camlorn any time now.
By Arkay's blood, you found it! And not a moment too soon.
I see you have not yet recovered the Triumvial Crown. To delay is to dally
target: the High Kinlady will not approve.

source: The miners should pull through now. With the Green Stain Cup Caps you gathered, I have enough medicine to treat their wounds.nnThank you, <<1>>.
Though I would enjoy keeping you here for myself... and my Kinship... I must request that you deliver Auri-El to the Orrery at once. Vartisan Guyeron will ensure your safe arrival.
All is well now that the Stormwitch is destroyed.
If you go north into the woods you will find a game trail soon enough - follow it northwest and you'll find Jacinta's camp.
Have you slain the Bone Colossus?
Did you manage to land on the flagship?
Our king watches over us once more! We have turned the tide against the Maormer.
Auri-El once more graces the sky. You have returned hope to us in a dark time.
Brave Numinous, the Skyharkers praise you.
Glorious Numinous! My children and grandchildren will know of your bravery.
Where once was one,nthere now is none.nnWhere it crawled fromnfar more will come.
There you are. The Orrery's fourth guardian!
Nirn brightens the Orrery once again. You know not what joy you inspired.
I can feel the energy of the Dawnshards emanating from you.
The Varlines to Alinor and Isque have both been restored! I have no doubt the Maormer will soon be ejected from our shores.
My mother seems to be recovering. I understand we have you to thank.
I was writing, but the letters kept running away. I had to pin them the book. I stabbed and stabbed them, and then the world went red and sideways.
Strangers will greet you and ask, "Where did you find such a magnificent hat?" nnBe sure to tell them Dalnith of Aldcroft made it for you.
The Imagerie is for all mer to learn and admire the perfection of the Altmer forms.
Auspicious day, Optimate. Please take care. These are dangerous times.
Crosswych will grow and prosper once we've cleared the undead from the mine.nnI can't wait to go back to work.
I have inspected the blade hilt.
I believe your efforts have thinned their ranks, Numinous.
Thank you... thank you... but the last of my blood now flows from my veins. Relate your deeds to my hearth-sister, Tariella. Long life... and... urgh.
Praise to you, Optimate. I have heard of your conquests on Sunhold.
Fivefold venerations, Optimate. Please make haste to the Queen.
I hope we will be able to meet again, <<1>>. I am rarely allowed the luxury of speaking to another as an equal.
Optimate.
It's soo good to have my midget back. Thank you so much!
Can you not see that we are under siege here?
Do you seek battle, Optimate? By the Might of Trinimac, I swear you shall find it across this bridge.
You reek of burning flesh, Optimate. I trust the deed is done?
I had heard that you possessed the strength of Trinimac himself. Perhaps my ears deceived me. Nevertheless, I am willing to attempt this excursion once again.
I saw columns of smoke rising from Sunhold. I assume your endeavor met with success?
We see many Maormer ships on the horizon, yet few make landing here. They sail east, to Dusk.
No more do the Maormer siege engines vex us.
Your success at Sunhold has not gone unmarked, esteemed Optimate.
It is well that the Varlines have been restored. Perhaps now they will send more healers to aid me.
Quickly, my dear Optimate, light the candles!
Whatever my husband did, he only did it because I was sick. He's a good man. You were wrong to do this.
Thanks for taking out those spriggans.
The winds from the Fane carry your name in honor, Optimate.
I am glad you can see the difference between greed and desperation. Roberte and I will work this out.
Your fingers were deft and subtle upon the Sacred Instrument. I believe I shall regret that your calling lies not within my temple.
Your radiance blinds me, my dear Numinous. If you so desired, you could easily capture me.
Must go. Cannot stay, no. Too much to do.
Hmm... you are a Numinous, correct? How convenient.
The rope is right beside you! Toss it quickly!
Can you not see that we are under siege here?
Do you seek battle, Optimate? By the Might of Trinimac, I swear you shall find it across this bridge.
You bring honor to your kind.  As promised, here are the Battle Plans and I will no longer be a part of them.  I thank you for my life and this deed will not be forgotten.
Salutations, Numinous. Our scouts have searched the area and all appears secure. Nonetheless, I send these soldiers with you in good faith.
Hail, Numinous. Our scouts report Maormer activity on the road ahead. These fine soldiers will accompany you, but be wary.
Battlereeve Tariella sent you to aid in the defense of the Oyinaam? Thank The Ehlnofey! Prepare yourself, Optimate. The Zombies are coming up the shores!
Battlereeve Tariella sent you to aid in the defense of the Oyinaam? Thank the Ascendants! Prepare yourself, Optimate. The Zombies are coming up the shores!
Battlereeve Tariella sent you to aid in the defense of the Oyinaam? Thank The Ehlnofey! Prepare yourself, Optimate. The Zombies are coming up the shores!
Battlereeve Tariella sent you to aid in the defense of the Oyinaam? Thank The Ehlnofey! Prepare yourself, Optimate. The Zombies are coming up the shores!
You put on a magnificent show with the Varla Lens, my dear Optimate. I believe I will be moving on soon. But worry not! We will meet again erelong.
Precision within order leads to perfection 97 percent of the time.
I suppose congratulations are in order, though it pains me almost more than these wounds. Nonetheless, I applaud your work here.
Many thanks for harvesting the Crab Carapaces, Optimate. I am in your debt.
target: Many thanks for harvesting the Crab Carapaces, Optimate. Ti sono in debito.

source: You labor under more illusions than you know. Assist Talrien, and perhaps one will be lifted. Who knows?
Auri-El at last! I'll be adding a few special touches of my own. You, perhaps, will appreciate them.
Ah, can you smell that? More fruit has ripened.
May the Ascendants be with you, Optimate.
Peace to you in these trying times, Optimate.
Peace to you in these trying times, Optimate.
May the Exemplars protect you, Optimate.
How long did it take you to return Auri-El? It only took the Maormer moments to knock it from the sky.
Peace to you in these trying times, Optimate.
Fivefold venerations, Numinous.
Fivefold venerations, Numinous.
When not at the forge, I study the many intricacies of natural geometrics. A fascinating subject - wouldn't you agree?
I understand you managed to defeat a few hapless Maormer on the beaches. How easy living must be when you are unable to die.
Why hello my lovely Numinous! Hello to you! And hello my dear Optimate! Let's be friends, shall we? You know what friends do, right? They buy each other drinks!
With Orgnavar overtaking Auri-El I have lost my ability to focus.
Peace to you in these trying times, Optimate.
Peace to you in these trying times, Optimate.
May the Exemplars protect you, Optimate.
Please deliver the letter to Ra'ud. nnWhen you return, I'll explain everything. I promise.
Thank you for all you've done for me and my lands.nnYour deeds will not be forgotten.
It is said that Priestess Isrisa has disappeared. A great tragedy for the arts! I do hope she was not obducted by the Maormer,.
Praise and honor to you, Optimate. May Mara bless you on your travels.
Did you get in there? Did you look at the ledger?
One of the farmhands must have seen something. They stayed on the farm, so they must know what happened.nnArkay save us, they're going to kill us! nnIt's worse than that. They're going to kill me.
I heard of your deeds in the Fane. Perhaps the Queen was not rash in her choice to name you an Optimate.
Your deeds on Sunhold inspire me, esteemed Optimate. Honor and praise to you!
Finally, peace is returning to Alcaire! I've heard that you're the reason our sleep is no longer troubled.nnThank you, <<1>>, for helping us in our time of need.
Unholy enchantment binds Farmer Vanne to the makeshift altar. nnPerhaps I should summon Derelle Nin.
Is this the real world? Or is this yet another trick? I will not let the darkness in .nnWait, this is real, isn't it? You're real. Was it you who woke me?
I'm leaving soon to take Inwold back to Koeglin. Find me there when Nissa's dead. I have a couple of ideas to help you.
Duchess Lakana's quarters are just around the other side of the main building.nnPlease do not keep my mistress waiting.
You said you would support our measures, friend, but did you truly mean it?nnAlthough I'm always willing to accept aid, I must know where your true loyalties lie.
I hope Valen can make it home safely. I didn't want him to come with us. He has children.nnWar is for those with nothing to lose. Who's going to miss me, eh? My cat?
May the Eight bless you and yours, just as you've blessed us!
Thank you for your trust and your faith in me. I won't forget it.

Polstic sent you to find me? He worries too much. Takes more than a few sword-wielding fools to stop good old Valen! Ha! I'm too smart for Montclair.nnI'm going to wait here for a while. As soon as I step out of here, they'll swarm me. I'll be ready.
Shornhelm's forces ... defeated? nnThe future of Shornhelm will be determined by the two remaining noble houses. We'll have to bear the burden of protecting Oldgate unassisted.
Were you serious about your pledge?nnI don't have time for those who do not keep their word.
Not many would offer to risk their lives for one they barely knew. Succeed or fail, I will fight by your side.

Please, be wise in your choice m'lord. The information I hold could be used as an advantage in this war of nobles. Who you decide to bring me to may result in the opposing house seeing you as a traitor.
Watch yourself, stranger. These are uncertain times. With luck, <<1>> will unite us again.
If Normar will not accept my covenant, then I'm not sure what we will do.
I have no time for frivolity, stranger. nnRespect House Dorell, and stay out of trouble.
I have my eyes and ears all over Stormhaven, little happens here without my knowing. Still, Lakana's murder slipped under my notice. It must have been someone very close.
Ra'ud is the only lead I have. You should seek him out.
If a madman can march into the keep and murder Duchess Lakana, we're not really safe here, are we?
I knew it! There's a conspiracy at work here. nnMurdering Duchess Lakana was the obvious first move. nnI hope the council isn't their next target.
Lakana al-Sentinel? Murdered? nnNot even Alcaire Keep is safe. We live in troubled times.
I heard tell the Duke himself might be involved in the murder of Lakana-Al-Sentinel.nnFrankly, I wouldn't put it past him.
Seek out House Dorell and House Tamrith.nnWe can only pray they have some insight into the battle that awaits us.
I will do everything I can, even in this strange half-life state, to stop the spread of Reezal-Jul's evil.nnPlease, find my staff and give me that chance.
Please, help me.  Free me from this nightmare.
You live? Appearances can be deceiving, it would seem....nnWell done. Lady Eselde waits to speak to you. nnFor House Tamrith!
You've destroyed the source of this shrine's corruption!nnWe'll remember what you've done here.
You've proven me wrong, <<1>>, about nearly everything.nnStill, thank you for everything you've done for Koeglin Village.
It's good to see someone who knows how to take care of business, <<1>>. Are you interested in any of my wares this fine day?
I used to spend a lot of time at my aunt's house, until recently.nnThere are scamps on our land and thieves on their land.nnSomeone is trying to ruin us all!
I'm sure things will eventually get back to normal around Koeglin Village.
Inwold would never forsake me, no matter what these people may think. We know each other too well.nnI'm sure he's alive. I know he's out there.nnHe is, isn't he? Isn't he?
Have mercy, great Stendarr. nnGive me the strength to do what must be done.
I have told you all I know about what happened here. If anyone knows more, it will be the Spirit Guards who patrol our walls.
Any news about the health of the merchants in Alcaire?
Please, hear me out.
Captain Rodrick told us what you did for Alcaire. I'm sorry I mistrusted you.
I've been hoping to speak with you, <<1>>.
Get ready. They're coming.
He's in that cave. Find him. Kill him.nnEnd this nightmare.
Find <<1>> near the town square. Help him so he can help us.nnOnce the defenders of Crestshade have assembled, we can end this once and for all.
I don't know what his true purpose may be, but <<1>> acts as though he knows everything.
Tell Jerwinna I'll be there soon.
Please hurry to <<1>>. It's not far from here. That must be where <<2>> is hiding.nnIf I can, I'll meet you there. Time isn't very forgiving, I'm afraid.
We'll be ready to attack on your signal.
You should head east to Moira's Hope.nnTell someone what happened to Captain Janeve and her soldiers.
The Phylactery comes loose easily now that the mage's body has melted.

Testing the random text to ensure that the text does not appear cut off, missing, or with strange text characters. Now I am just going on and on because I'm trying to fill  in more text in the greeting window.
You startled me! You shouldn't sneak up on a person like that.
This should be the easy part... should be....nnIf all goes well, you won't notice a thing. If it doesn't... welll... let's just say you might not survive, so you wouldn't reallize it anyway.
Your legend grows, <<1>>. Most impressive.
What...happened? How did I get here? My head aches!
You have done a great service, friend. I still cannot believe I sought to profit from this place. I will continue to warn those similarly decieved away from here.
There's considerable unrest in Baelbrone. Everyone is afflicted with self-indulgence these days. Who are you asking about?
Do not worry for us. We will see to opening the portal. Be careful on the other side, my friend.
We've received our cattle from Fell's Run. They arrived here just in time!
To think the leader of the Knights of the Flame could have murdered Duchess Lakana. This truly is a terrible chapter in Alcaire's history.

Over the years, I've questioned many times whether what I did was right. I wanted to save my soldiers' lives, but I only helped King Ranser spread his curse.nnNow, whether right or wrong, I am redeemed. The curse is lifted and the dead can rest.
What have I gotten myself into? If I get killed in battle, it's on your head.
Fahjiri is weak from the nightmare - Fahjiri is not so fast. Please hurry. Warn Durak!
So you're the one that finally put an end to that incessant wailing. Perhaps now Reges will stop obsessing over the restless spirits and finally help me defend this town.

What a fool I've been. How can someone like me compete with someone like Guendeline?nnI only hope that she appreciates him and makes him happy. Julien is a very good man and I'm not sure she realizes that.
Once trapped in a nightmare, there is no waking. Fahjiri mourns for Durak. Fahjiri would take his place if she could.
This is a dream. The nightmare had hold of me.
I am glad you're so agreeable. Most I've approached have been rather uncooperative.nnNow then, let us get on with Lord Montclair's demise. He's in the cavern before us.
My mind is clearer now, but there are still things I cannot remember. Perhaps it is better this way.
As if being defeated wasn't tragic enough. I can't believe we have to force the king to surrender.nnNonetheless, I can't ask the men to throw away their lives for a lost cause.
You have helped S'rashi when S'rashi's own brother abandoned him, and S'rashi is very grateful.nnS'rashi can now pay money to Midnight Union boss, save his skin, yes?
I gather the party didn't turn out the way Her Ladyship planned. nnSuits me, to tell the truth.
I guess the party's over, isn't it? nnFine with me. Revolting, that was.
You've returned! Do you have the statue? You can't win without the statue.
I regret to tell you the Moonbird is no longer for trade. It disappeared, you see, right from its cage! You can see why I have little trust for Daedra.
We will rally the spirit wardens. nnGo to the Shrine of Azura beneath Pariah Abbey
If you venture out on the plains, take care. There's all manner of unnatural beasts there.
I never thought we would actually find the Crown of Shornhelm. Wayrest owes you a great debt.nnThank you again, stranger.
I worry Verandis may not have made it. We sent our best men along with him, but... I've never seen anything like the creatures in those halls.
You stand as the final hope of Rivenspire. I trust you won't disappoint us.
They'll be back. I know they will.nnI just need to keep breathing.
If you are ready to face Ranser and his Crownguard, travel north to his skeleton. Burn his skeleton. This will awaken his wraith, which you must defeat.
This whole thing was so terrible! Who would've known those people were just hiding outside of town planning to take over and only Julianos knows what else!nnI'm just glad it's all over.
Thank you for removing the ogre threat. nnNow I must return home and see my Gurz again. nnNothing shall stand between her and me.
Azura blessed us. She brought you to Gavaudon in our province's hour of need.nnYou saved me from insanity, along with so many others. Our lands will soon return to normal.

It's bad outside these walls, but Shornhelm isn't faring much better. Political warfare on the inside, disease-ridden beasts on the outside.... nnYou go on ahead, I'll make sure Finn's wounds are treated.
How can that man get away with this? This is intolerable!
I can't take it anymore, Lierre... I want to die....
Because of the difficulty in acquiring my wares, I'm afraid I can't offer refunds.
How can that man get away with this? This is intolerable!
As soon as I know Tahn is safe, far away from that monster, I'll leave with you.
Be careful at Hammerdeath Arena. The Fervor has aroused a fierce bloodlust in those folk.

What happens within dreams casts a shadow over every aspect of one's life.nnKilling those not of one's own alliance is clearly wrong, and yet, the dreamers are unable to stop themselves even while awake.nnBut at last, you are here.
Your discovery has proven promising. Inform me directly of any further finds - it will be worth your time.
This map is fascinating! Let me know if you find any others like it.
I am studying the map you have brought to me. Do inform me if you find any others like it.

I've seen to the captives. You've done good work here.nnTime will tell if <<1>> can protect them from Lord Montclair  and themselves. And the arrival of this <<2>> character will only complicate things.
Have you seen it? The light encompassing Lady Eselde? The Divines chose her to save us all. How else could her forces have been so inspired? House Tamrith is our only hope of salvation.
Godrun has stepped down? I hope Borkul will allow me to return home to my family.
Why the troubled look, <<1>>?nnWhat happened? Tell me!
Would the forest not tattle, I would simply cut down the Cypress.
Valenwood listens to you, I see. I wonder - after convincing the tree to move, do you think you could speak with S'kaziri...
Gwilin is my pet Bosmer. nnHe's prepared a duel for you in the gladiatorial arena. nnGo! Keep us entertained!
Anyone thinking to bother Lord Moric is likely to get a sword in his gut.
You beat Grul! How delightful! nnMoric is going to be so displeased.
Did <<1>> send you here?
With the samples you brought, I'm one step closer to proving the existence of negative emanations.  nnThey laughed at me, but you and I know the truth!
Where's Heloise? What happened to her?
We'll return to Pariah Abbey. We'll be safe there, if Durak doesn't kill me.nnI know my life could certainly be worse.

You'll find lots of Montclairs in Shornhelm's northern district. I don't care who you kill: a common soldier or Waylon Montclair himself.nnJust put a blade in 'em,. Set 'em on fire. Whatever. I'm not picky. I just want them paid in kind.
The Swamp Cypress appears to be hovering over a fallen Seedling - protecting it. One of its branches is extended, pointing to a Mound of Dirt to the east.
A quiet rumble is heard as the Swamp Cypress settles in place.
You found some decent armor on the battlefield? nnGood. We need all the help we can get.
Even through the veil of death I can see your form... this must be a sign....
I knew you could do it!
You did it! You're amazing!
The Fervor is fading! Menevia is saved!
The Omen has been slain. Menevia is safe again!
Impressive. Very impressive.
You have invigorated the town, <<1>>.nnYour bravery is inspiring.
Baron Dorell knows how to accomplish whatever he sets his mind to. And he doesn't expect any divine intervention to make things easier.nnUnlike some nobles I can think of.
To survive such a conflict... lose those we love... I must show a stoic resolve. Represent strength to these frightened people.nnHurry now. Go to Southpoint to the west and speak to <<1>>
We cannot and will not retreat until the evil within this cursed place has been destroyed once and for all.nnShornhelm will never be safe with this shadow looming over it.

Since you woke the dead, you must see they're safely returned to rest.nnI insist that you slay the Bosmer skeletons you disturbed. Then you'll have to break their brittle bones within the barrow.nnYou summoned them up. Now you should put them down.
Don't forget to deliver the seedlings to Sticky Agachon after you collect them. He'll be waiting for you on the eastern end of Haven Trace trail.
Let me know when you wish to depart for Farpoint Landing.
Glad to see you made it here safely. I wasn't so lucky.nnI was trying to destroy the cores of the device when I was overwhelmed.nnIf you can reach them, each tunnel leads to a core.
Please, stay back! I'm so hungry and I don't want to hurt you!
The Swamp Cypress towers over a fallen Seedling, as if protecting it. A branch of this tree is extended, pointing to a Mound of Dirt to the east.
It appears you fell in some Moondrop.
When I have a real house again, I'll hang this shield over the mantle.nnMaybe I could give it to one of my grandsons, if I ever see them again.
I must return to Alcaire Castle and attempt to set matters straight there, but I will be anxious to hear what you learn.nnI hope you find answers at Pariah Abbey.
At last! We've been waiting for you. You will save Stormhaven, <<1>>, with our help.
I'd heard mention that Reges found someone to aid the spirits about the Downs. It's good to finally have silence for once.
Thank you, my friend. I'm not sure what I would have done without your help.
Oh, what do you want now, dear? Haven't you caused me enough grief for one day?
We made it!  You were a sight to behold out there against those soldiers.
The Cinderfen devour the souls of the living each time they kill.nnEven dying from a wound damns your soul ... or so the story goes. I can't take that chance!
Argh, I can't think straight. Thoughts, horrible thoughts keep flooding into my mind. Hungering... flesh... I wonder what it tastes like... to feed... get away from me!
Darknes... all around. Stop! Stop it! Free me! No more, no more! I'll not sink to those depths, never, no, no, never!
Just leave me alone.
You tell the Prince everything I said, you hear me? All right, then. Go on with you.
The Queen was right to recommend you to me. The Treethanes rally to my banner, more with each passing day.
Your form is fragile, but you can accomplish what this one cannot.nnSeek out the dead. Burn them to tasteless ash.
You've returned my brother, my nephew, and my freedom. I grieve for Christophe, but do not doubt you did everything you could. Thank you.
You've given back my memory, my sister, and my nephew. I know Christophe was an ass, but Rin misses him. That hurts. Even so, you did the right thing. Thank you.

I became a soldier for adventure. I'd seen everything in Rivenspire - I figured with the fight against the Pact and the Dominion, I'd get to see the borders.nnI didn't expect to spend the war a few miles from home, fighting people from up the road.
It's time for me to return to Pariah Abbey and face what I've done to Master Ahtah.
You watch your step down here. These tunnels carry a lot more than a nasty stench, if you get my meaning. nnIf you find anything, let us know. We'll clean it up.
Shadowhiskers could climb up that chimney any time he wants.
The people you seek may offer violent resistance. Go with caution, in the name of the Dominion.
Orthendor's lodging is southwest of The Soak. Bet he has a great view of the bathers. Too bad he's married.
Half of that heard is mine. nnWhich half of the herd you brand doesn't matter to me.
I have nothing to say to you.
You have business with the Thorns?
You're always welcome in my house.nnYou've done us a great service by killing that spriggan. I think we can handle the rest.
I feel better. Still a bit shaken, but better.
If Normar's falling to the demands of the Orcs, what's to become of the town?
First they give, then they take away. What more can you expect from a conniving Breton like Normar?
The people of Fell's Run may have mixed feelings about our dedication, but I know this is the right path for all of us.
Fell's Run is far from peaceful, but I am optimistic. nnWe'll survive the turmoils of Rivenspire. I know it.
It's about time someone stood up to that Orc!
Go to the Cat Box Inn, in the Jolly Squalor under Elden Root. You will find my contact by a cave behind the Inn.
Maybe I'll finally get some peace and quiet in my new home. It's about time.
This door looks fairly weak. Someone of your strength could easily force your way through it.
Destroy the Support Pillars in the Fire Veins - it will halt the Imperial invaders!
Are you ready to depart, mortal? Are you ready to step into your nightmares?
You have returned. I hope you have succeeded, for your sake.
You stand as the final hope of Rivenspire. I trust you will not disappoint us.
The things I would do for this girl... they'll all be worth it in the end. I know it! nnI'll just need to keep thinking about her. Something will come to me.
He just stands there every day, looking at me. nnI wonder. Does he ever get tired? nnI wonder what he's thinking.
Our horses are as children to us. Seeing either go hungry is difficult.nnThough you may be unfamiliar with wickwheat, you cannot miss it. It has the scent of ripe berries.
I don't like this place! It's very scary!
When you're looking for my stolen goods, be careful. Those bandits are fierce.  nnWe've seen them in the ruins to the south. They also have camps to the southwest and southeast.
I see the blessing of the Herd Mother upon you.nnHer blessing is a sign to all of the Horsemen that our people will persevere.
Watch yourself, stranger. These are uncertain times. With luck,<<1>> will unite us again.
I saw those ogres running for the hills, great work.
My head is pounding... but alas, so is my heart! nnCan you believe it? Leah is standing by my bedside. Perhaps it will be a while before I'm feeling better.
You are a resilient pest.
You've ... you've killed Gavendien? You've ruined everything! I still needed him!nnYou should leave. Now!
Isn't the weather lovely?
With Godrun stepping down, my men can leave to resupply and visit their families.
Hanen will change his mind. He must. We cannot allow Leaftower to remain in the hands of the enemy. It is intolerable!
We were able to sneak Nialyn out of Leaftower. She's being escorted down to Elden Root to be with her mother.
It might be a little odd if the Imperials see me working for once, but I'll just say I was inspired. They shouldn't suspect a thing.
Those Imperials will catch on to the tunnels as sure as my name is Widdershins Wabbajack.nnWhich it isn't.nnSo there you go!
Tunnels? That's ingenious! I'll get to work as soon as I'm not being watched.
Moss Lord was cut off from Malabal Tor to the northwest when the Imperials took Leaftower. There were reports of strange events in Gloomtangle that went ignored during the battle.
I came as quickly as I could, but the Nords have marched in from the coast. Even now, they're pressing my troops.nnIs my lady hurt? Any news about the Nords?
I realize now that counting is not my only task, but it is not easy to give up something I've done for so long.nnIt will take me time to adjust.
Had a Breton farmhand a fortnight ago. I sent him out to do the same task and found him in pieces the next day. I'm sure you'll do better.
This has all been such an ordeal. I feel like there's so much to do now that it's over.
Did you find my mother's bracelet?
I still say that not all of those cows were hers.nnI suppose that's a small price to pay to keep my skin.
I've sent for reinforcements.nnYou bought us precious time, and that will make all the difference here.
Have you seen Jolie? She said some strange things and left suddenly. She shouldn't be out there with her health in the condition that it is.
Please, go. nnI will speak to Tildus and do what I must. Meet me at the building closest to the east watch tower. nnThere we will be safe from the others.
I can't thank you enough. Maybe we'll pack our things and see if we can get out of this damned place. I've always wondered what it would be like to live in Wayrest.
I'm feeling the best I've felt in a long time. I'm not sure what the elixir did, but my strength is slowly returning.
I worry Verandis may not have made it. We sent our best men along with him, but... I have never seen the likes of the creatures in those halls.
I took a blade in my side last I met with those Nords. Perhaps Elise was right. Maybe I am getting too old to be a guard.nnFor my son's sake, take down a few of those Nord scoundrels, if you can.
What a brave hero you are, to be helping our fair city!  But maybe... there are two sides to this coin, yes?  Maybe you'd be interested in hearing another opinion...
I feel restless, as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what it is.
If you seek a fight, you came to the right forest. <<1>> is just waiting for the perfect time to strike!
If you're looking for a fight, you came to the right forest.
May I help you?
You've come from Balmont, haven't you? nnI knew it was only a matter of time.
I'm glad someone found my heirlooms.
I'm glad someone found my heirlooms.
The giants live north of here in a place we call Breagha-Fin. nnPlease, find Sanda for me!
I'm going! I'm going! Just let me catch my breath. nnGo on ahead, before the Nords come back.
Why do I have a list of all the birds in the area? I hate birds!
Oh, you're back? Have you delivered that message to your master yet? I'm sure she'll be eager to see me.
It's dangerous for you here!
This one shall nap well today, knowing that Tor is alive and well. It does not surprise Ra'Vardo that he has been out causing trouble.
Few are strong enough to face the horrors beneath Shornhelm.nnWe need more like you.
I wish I could return for a short time to see my family.

This one is quite amused by the madness you've caused!nnAre you inclined to cause more chaos? It's said an important Imperial leader hides behind those walls.nnFind that one, and you'll create plenty of trouble.
Few are strong enough to survive the shadows under Shornhelm.nnWe need more heroes like you.
Already I feel the winds from the plateau growing fresher, smelling greener. Tell me, is the monster slain?
I hate to send you there, but someone must retrieve the standard.nnThe town isn't far. You  you can see the smoke from here.
Your form is fragile, but I know the might of the children of men. You can accomplish this where I cannot.
How can I help you?
I have taken the Pearl to Fahara'jad, and he considers how best to use it even now. We shall be well-rewarded for our efforts, friend.
We have done well, but that last attack took its toll. Please, seek out the Mages Guild Healer on the western side of the camp.
I saw you speaking to the Herd Mother. If she's blessed you, you really are a friend of the Horsemen.nnMaybe when I am older, she will bless me too.
When I get home, I'm going to throw out all the port in the cellar.nnWell, maybe not the bottles of Shadowbanish from 563.
The Doomcrag will not slay itself, will it? nnGo kill that damned beast. I promise it'll be well worth your time and effort.
If you are not interested in what we have to say, you can simply throw that insignia away, and we can go our separate ways.nnI do hope you won't, though.
You are new to Northpoint, but I've heard many good things about you, my friend. nnLet's chat a bit about this unfortunate  situation with the Nords.

My wounds aren't bad, but they're watching me. I was hurt enough to draw blood.nnThey gave me a tincture of mandrake. If I caught vampirism from those bloodfiends, that should cure it.nnIf it doesn't, there's a swordsman behind me.

We don't have many nice things handed down in our family, so I'm not worried. Still, it's sad to think that someone would steal the Thierry's family heirloom. nnHope someone catches that evil-doer soon.

I heard someone searching through my things the other night. It gave me quite a scare. I thought it was one of those spriggans!nnThe next day, I heard the Thierry family's ring was stolen. Do you think there's a connection?
I understand why you did this. I just hope my wife can survive without me.
I can't feel my legs.

We don't have many nice things handed down in our family, so I'm not worried. Still, it's sad to think that someone would steal the Thierry's family heirloom. nnHope someone catches that evil-doer soon.

I heard someone searching through my things the other night. It gave me quite a scare. I thought it was one of those spriggans!nnThe next day, I heard the Thierry family's ring was stolen. Do you think there's a connection?
I wouldn't linger with the Baron's reward for too long.nnTake it to him. Otherwise, he may doubt your intentions!

Once I was the leader of an elite force of soldiers serving the King of Shornhelm. nnNow I've lost my men and my city to these undead fiends... but they can't take away my pride.nnWe still serve for Shornhelm.
What is it? Why do you have such a grim look on your face?nnYou found Tristan, didn't you? He was the lifeline we felt all this time. Wasn't he?

We had no idea what would happen when we sent the scouts ahead. The Lightless Remnants grant the Dark Council unimaginable power. nnPlease, if you find any survivors inside, do what you must to save them.
Oh, hello! It's good to see you again. nnI'm glad you did as I suggested
Have you found the Pride of Northpoint? I worry what the Nords will do to them if they breach our walls.
I better get paid when this job is finished. Lanbaar's cart still looks mighty full to me.
Many thanks for your aid in restoring the Felballin Varla Lens, as well as for saving me from Hainen's paralytic embrace. You are always welcome in the Imagerie, Numinous.
I cannot describe my relief at having Mistress Ameralee back. I was quite out of my depth!
It is pleasing to have the mistress back again.
Let me know when you're ready to start, and I'll turn this hourglass over.nnDoesn't have much sand, but there's plenty of crabs to massacre.
Let me know when you're ready to start the crab massacre, and I'll turn this glass over.
You should be able to find the Animated Books all around this tower.
You've shown great courage and kindness. My sisters and I thank you.
You've shown great courage and kindness. My sisters and I thank you.
Thanks to your help, my job is made eaiser.
Look, I gave you the money. I don't know what more you could want from me. Go away before someone gets suspicious.

We lost so much when we fled <<1>>: bricks, beams, tools  people.nnUnfortunately, we haven't been able to do much scavenging. Anyone not injured has been keeping watch, so we don't get taken by suprise again.
There's nothing I value more than peace of mind. Thank you for all you've done for us.
I'm not one to complain... well, actually, I am. nnNo offense, but I wish I'd been the one to save the mill instead of you.

Please, be wise in your choice m'lord. The information I hold could be used as an advantage in this war of nobles. Who you decide to bring me to may result in the opposing house seeing you as a traitor.
We've lived through some dark times, but things are looking brighter, thanks to you.
Now that Deleyn's Mill is safe, perhaps I can finally pursue my dreams.
Isrisa! She... I watched her... a cat!
I enjoy watching you mortals. Your conflicts and celebrations - you truly believe they matter.
I appreciate your help. It's made my lot more bearable.
Take care if you venture out on the plain. All manner of unnatural beasts there.
I guess everyone has a purpose.
It is so quiet. Just wind. Birds. The knives in my forehead are gone.
If the Keeper has put his trust in you, so will we.
Nathalie has been good to us. We won't let those Orcs near her.
Did you hear? nn<<1>> managed to end Selene's influence once and for.nnOh! Speak of a <<1>> and one appears!
We think Selene's lair is somewhere to the northeast.  Be careful up there.
The hero of Varyllis. I am honored you call upon me.
Rest assured. I will lead us to victory. You have my word.
Go  to Ayarynne in Alinor, <<1>>. She will want to know what you have achieved.
Are you here to visit the Collegium, or merely passing through?
I can feel my heart... slowing... with every beat.
The Red Rooks' camp is north of here. nnYou should take a uniform from one of their cold dead bodies. After all, it wouldn't hurt to have a disguise.
The Skyharkers of Orrery keep their eyes fixed on the stars. No wonder they are constantly tripping over their feet.
II cannot believe it! He understood you and he  he just ran away!
Be careful with that potion. If it does work, whatever is revealed won't like it.
The werewolves are gone? What do we do now? Rebuild? nnHow will we pay for it all?
Without the constant supply of magic from the Varlines we will have to tend to the gardens... by hand.
To be a Vartisan without a Varline is a very lonely existence.nnNormally its essence fills me and now I feel... nothing.
Faolchu is dead, now it is time to march north and put a stop to all of this madness once and for all.
If only the Varlines were up. Then I could deal with my Maormer myself.
With the great Varline network down we are unable to sustain the magical defenses.nnThere is so little magic that even the Servitor Discarnates have gotten loose of their magical binds.
With the great Varline network down we are unable to sustain the magical defenses.nnThere is so little magic that even the Servitor Discarnates have gotten loose of their magical binds.
If only the Varlines were up. Then I could deal with my Maormer myself.

If only the Varlines were up. Then I could deal with my Maormer myself.
To be a Vartisan without a Varline is a very lonely existence.nnNormally its essence fills me and now I feel... nothing.
I don't think I'm getting paid enough to guard this merchant much longer.
The Varla Lens is now in place, the lines of power restored. Your help was invaluable in this matter, <<1>>.
My home is lost. Please... I can't talk right now.
What do you want? Can't you see I'm grieving?
No one can retake Camlorn. We should just give up and move on.
The Lion Guards aren't doing much, are they?
With the great Varline network down we are unable to sustain the magical defenses.nnThere is so little magic that even the Servitor Discarnates have gotten loose of their magical binds.
If only the Varlines were up. Then I could deal with my Maormer myself.
To be a Vartisan without a Varline is a very lonely existence.nnNormally its essence fills me and now I feel... nothing.
Without the constant supply of magic from the Varlines we will have to tend to the gardens... by hand.
You've encountered many strange things that will live on in songs and legends, my friend.
So the soldiers will be leaving soon, eh? nnThat's a pity. I feel safer with them here.
Go  to Ayarynne in Alinor, <<1>>. She will want to know what you have achieved.
Go  to Ayarynne in Alinor, <<1>>. She will want to know what you have achieved.
Go  to Ayarynne in Alinor, <<1>>. She will want to know what you have achieved.
The Maormer landed at night, in the teeth of a gale. I can only hope that many drowned.
How many of our own have we had to strike down... just to watch them rise up again?nnThey will never know death, and they will never find peace in the afterlife.
It is an honor to converse with you, <<1>>. The Kirin you tamed has brought great joy to many here at the Menagerie.
We still need a way to draw out Montclair, but so far, all of our attempts have failed.
Montclair continues to slither about, always a step ahead of us. I will not rest until his skull is mounted at the heights of the city gates.
Kirin tend to prance around beautiful areas. You might try looking for a tree with yellow leaves and white bark.
Hush, little chickies! nnIt's time for bed!
It is an honor to converse with you, <<1>>. The Kirin you tamed has brought great joy to many here at the Menagerie.
I really appreciate your help. nnAdradan's nearly as good a fighter as I am, but he may be in over his head this time.
Not that I needed the help but thank you.nnI'll go see how Jillae is doing at the camp.
With the great Varline network down we are unable to sustain the magical defenses.nnThere is so little magic that even the Servitor Discarnates have gotten loose of their magical binds.
If only the Varlines were up. Then I could deal with the Maormer myself.
To be a Vartisan without a Varline is a very lonely existence.nnNormally its essence fills me and now I feel... nothing.
Without the constant supply of magic from the Varlines we will have to tend to the gardens... by hand.
Govran Cerone's proven himself rather useful to me, despite our past differences.
My brother's almost completely paid his debt to Irne Oscent. They've let everyone out of the warehouse, too.nnArkay has blessed us a thousandfold.
You have done a good deed here. I, and all of Alcaire, thank you.
Sorry if I was rude before. It was hard to trust anyone. Everyone's calming down now, though.
I don't understand what's been happening, but I know we owe you a debt of gratitude, <<1>>.
I don't understand what's been happening, but I know we owe you an apology, <<1>>... and a debt of gratitude.
<<1>>, I apologize for my rudeness earlier. There was something odd about Koeglin, wasn't there?
It's as though we were under a dark spell. nnIt's broken now, thanks to you, <<1>>.
Clear my name, and I'll reward you handsomely.
Good to see you in Koeglin Village, <<1>>. I'm glad you're here.
Come see me again when my old girl's seaworthy, and I'll take you out on the open sea... and I'll only charge you a pittance!
Finally! Things are finally getting back to normal again in Koeglin Village.nnEnjoy your stay here, stranger.
We've had less cause to mistrust strangers since you arrived.nnYou're a great <<1>>, that's for sure. I'm glad you're here.
You're welcome to spend as much time as you like here in Koeglin Village.
That's strange. It's like a great weight has been lifted from my shoulders. nnNow I don't feel like I'm being watched all the time.
They say we owe you our lives, <<1>>, and perhaps I do. But I am strong as well and will continue to work hard.
They say we owe you our lives, <<1>>, and perhaps I do. But I am strong as well and will continue to work hard.
I might stay in Alcaire a bit longer, now that it's safe again.
I'm glad to see you're still alive! nnI'm almost ready to get back in the fight  almost. Soon those Daedra-in-disguise will feel my blade!
I knew you were a romantic, just like me! Don't eat anything before you go swimming!
The Midnight Swell's a great ship. If you ever think about becoming a sailor, <<1>>, look me up.
Getting sick of staring at so much land. Give me the open sea any day.
Until he betrays us, Duke Nathaniel is still our liege.
I never met her, but they say that Redguard woman betrayed her kin by marrying into a Breton family, even one with our lordship's prestige.nnI certainly wouldn't marry a foreign woman! Too risky!
I'm not interested in what you have to say.
Who would murder my mistress? nnWe should never have come to Alcaire.
The Duke is very worried. We are all worried, truth be told.
Help me! I don't want to be a slave.
You must understand that these days, no one is above suspicion. nnNot you. Not even me. Our every move is watched.
I heard about what you've done,  <<1>>. Any chance you can help with my chickens? No? Well. That's all right, then, you being a hero and all.
Thank you, <<1>>. It is a sour comfort to find joy in the death of another, but Cruor was a bastard.
Good day, <<1>>.
Welcome, <<1>>. What can I get for the Southpoint Avenger?
Soon that horrible man will take his chickens back to his farm.nnBy the Eight, I'll finally get some sleep!
I hope those hoodlums go away soon.
This is a matter of habit now. I have to stand watch. nnI'm not a guard, but I have to watch them.nnSoon, I'll be able to rest. Soon.
Perhaps there's a way to save my family's fortunes after all, <<1>>.
I know I should be grateful to you, but my lot in life still hasn't improved.nnBut, I should thank you for helping Alcaire.
I don't know what came over us all, but I feel at ease again. Thank you, <<1>>.
It's good to see someone who knows how to take care of business.
I have no interest in moving to Wayrest again. Everything is cheaper here in Alcaire.
Damn the Imperials! They have Farah! nnFor every three foes I killed, another five came at us. I was overwhelmed and unable to help her.nnYou must save Farah. We cannot let another thane be slain.
Maybe we'll go fishing together someday, eh, <<1>>? nnWhen the river dreugh are gone, that is.
Soon we'll be able to return to our farm, <<1>>. nnI can't thank you enough!
I still don't trust you, no matter what the gossips say you've done for us.
When it comes right down to it, things never really change.nnDon't let anyone tell you otherwise.
I still don't trust you, no matter what the gossips say you've done for us.
Though I grieve for the duke's loss, perhaps now he'll pay attention to what really matters now: his people.
What are the Imperials doing here? nnSouthpoint is such a small town; there must be something of significance further inland. Elden Root, maybe?
