You are being praised as the Southpoint Avenger. I suspect I am speaking to a legend...nnThank you, <<1>>.

The Daedric Princes work in strange ways, but this has gone too far. They've taken everything away from me. nnTheir prince is lurking among the spotted demons now. I must be careful. nnI must be very, very careful.
Hair.nnHair!nnPfaugh! Imperials are stupid, silly creatures. If they had real fur, maybe they'd stop thinking hair is treasure, eh?
There's no denying the tragedy of war, when you see so many slain over a bit of sand and rock. Might as well make the best of it, though!
What do you want, stranger?

Thanks for finding my mother and bringing her home safely, <<1>>. nnI don't know how we'd survive without my mother... especially her cooking.nnMy sister is a rotten cook. I think she's trying to kill us.
Thanks for helping out the crew of the Midnight Swell, <<1>>. nnMy brother should be here soon. Then we can go on to Daggerfall!nnI thought Stormhaven would be safe, but clearly, I was mistaken.
The little ones will be so pleased with their mother's finds today. They just love playing dress-up soldier!
You must be the one Giras mentioned. nnI need not introduce Rain-Whisper to you, for it seems you two have already met. nnHe has revealed much about a matter I thought was resolved long ago.
Get out of my sight before I call the guards.

Councilor Bravosi can be found in the kinhouse to the west. He speaks with a gilded tongue, so watch his words carefully.nnIt pains me to see our city chafe under the grip of fear. I do not know what House Dres thinks to fix by dividing our people.
Ah... the scent of fresh corpses, mingled with the salty tang of sea breeze. Smells like profit to me!

I must inform Miluru immediately, before she finds out on her own. Please, send her my apologies for my poor handling of this matter.nnI will leave Bravosi to her hands. I have enough to deal with already!
The Southpoint Avenger!
You've returned, and in fine health, I can see. Did you go to Fort Arand?
When it comes right down to it, things never really change. nnDon't let anyone tell you otherwise.
Southpoint will be rebuilt stronger than before and none will forget the bravery of the Southpoint Avenger!
I hope Cruor died slowly...
Prices seem to be going down again, ever since you helped the duke, <<1>>. nnWe owe you a debt we can never repay.
May Cruor's corpse rot uneaten.
You've brought damnation upon us all. nnWe'll have no part in this sickness. My people are suffering.nnWe will see your kind pay for this!
With that blasted mudcrab dead, maybe poor old eelmer like me can start trapping in the harbor.nnAs soon as the damned Imperials are driven out, anyway. Hmph.
You infiltrated the palisade and assassinated the Imperial leader...nnImpressive feat, <<1>>.
Those Oscent boys have always been trouble. nnI wanted to poison them, but I can see that would be wrong. nnAfter all, that might be bad for business.
Many stray spirits have been inducted into the ranks of our guardians. nnEven graverobbers can serve a purpose in death.nnThis pleases me, <<1>>.
Nori-ja doesn't want to know what's making those noises in the woods. She will stay in town and do her best imitation of a rock. A very small, unappetizing rock.

You have come for survivors of the Blightstorm? Valiant for one not blessed by Meridia. nnTake this token of the soldiers as proof of your brave deed, stranger. Your fortitude may shield you from the Blight, but there are other dangers about.
What creature compells me to return to this plane? Tell me, <<1>>, why do you torture me so?!
Do you know the power you wield with that amulet? nnAre you another Dres assassin sent to destroy me?
Extinguish the brazier. Too many have already died.
I grieve for Sir Croix and all those who died fighting for him, but there was no other way to save the Knights of the Flame.nnThank you for doing what I could not.
Please retrieve the Muckspung Elixir for Tsajivi. It can be found in the boat to the southeast of here.
Have you started your trial?  The altars to Meridia are around the conclave.
That was amazing!  I've never seen anyone fight like that, whether or not they have Meridia's blessing which it seems that you do, my friend.
Such amateurs. If the Camonna Tong believes I'd fall for this, they must really think I'm not fit for my position.
Have you found the packages?
Now I just need to get this cart fixed and I'm heading to Wayrest. City's big enough that I don't think I have to worry about a bunch of local merchants trying to chase me around with pitch forks.
You could be working for the slavers, looking to befriend us only to betray us later. Ahjiivi will speak to you when you have killed our persecutors.
You look like a reasonable <<1>> - please, listen to what I have to say.
You're not from Southpoint are you? I've lived here all my life - I'd tell you how long that was if I could count.
If you see any Bosmer in the woods to the east, report it immediately.
My pants! I knew you would not fail me, <<1>>!
Come now, I know I'm enchanting, but we shouldn't keep Mazhe pantless much longer.
Get away from my find, stranger. This poor boy belongs to me, now... or at least what's left of him does.
I've not been so amused in at least half a day! Well done, my friend, well done!
These caves have been quiet for so long, but the winds have returned and our spirits with them.nnYou walk among the living, yet you speak to the dead. Will you help return us to rest?
I must say, I've never been so glad to be accosted by someone before. nnYour dance was something... quite special.
What a show, my friend, what a show! Thank Arkay we moved those stinking dreugh eggs out of here. Can you imagine being surrounded by such awful creatures?nnGo, and be merry!
It's rare to find such a good dancer. Please express my pleasure to Lady Dominique.
Please tell Jaqspur Ina to return with the other Jaqspur. We need food... badly.nnYou'll find her inside the Thrambles.
What news? Have you thoroughly grizzled our enemies?

Thunderbugs are nice, as wildlife goes around here. They gather in the high places of the Thrambles and build nests in the tree roots.nnThey keep to themselves, but they will attack anyone who disturbs their offspring.
You're a monster! nnHow could you leave them behind? nnI'd hunt you, but that would be a waste of a good arrow.
I know I have to go home soon, but the heat is so relaxing.
I've heard about you, <<1>>. I'll follow your example of business before pleasure shortly... right after I finish lounging in the hot springs.
I heard fighting. nnAre you okay?
The lamia attacks seem fewer. What news have you of the poison?

Talk to me again when your armor is stained with the blood of the dreugh.nnThey're skulking near the springs. They want to foul its waters by laying their eggs along the shore.nnThat cannot happen. You must not let that happen.
We can't make it to Omaynia without your help.... No, Ahjiivi, don't leave us to die!

Sugar's going to kill me... or I'll die right here. Can't decide what's better. Ahjiivi can't have made it to Omaynia. Bet that n'wah is dying of the Blight right now.nnWho's there? Get away! I won't let you finish me off!
Just unlock the chains that bind me. nnI'll be gone quicker than a Khajiit on Bathing Day.
My dad keeps making a big to-do about coming back to work.
The murder of Cruor won't rebuild our town, but it eliminates a dangerous threat.nnThank you, <<1>>.
Huzzah! It's <<1>>, the Southpoint Avenger!
<This hen doesn't have bright blue eyes. It couldn't have swallowed Belene's wedding ring.>
It's as though I've been kept under a spell. Then you came to Menevia! Now I'm under your spell....nnWhere has the time gone? I must go home soon.
What is your birthsign, traveller? Mine is the Thief.nnAfter all, I love to steal the hearts of beautiful women....
Oh Jory... poor, poor Jory. He was so young! So innocent!

Thank you, <<1>>, for talking to William. I've heard him whistling again like he used to, before the madness swept over him.nnYou're welcome to sup with us any time. Ganise is learning how to make stew; we always have extra.
You found my old locket. Thank you for bringing it back to me, <<1>>. Many would have just sold it.
I can't discuss the charges brought against Llameni at this time.
Go quickly. nnThey'll hide all the evidence they can.nnWe must act before our accusations fall on the Tribunal's ears.
You! You are not one of House Dres! You must help me, before it is too late!
You wouldn't think it from their appearance, but <<1>>s are delicious.
Has someone been informing <<1>> of the Scavenger Hunt?
Speak with her for me! nnMy overwhelming desire for Lady Diane affects my ability to think with a clear head, let alone speak to her.nnI can't even speak to her.
Encouraging the stranger. nnReferring him to Elder Knonk in the cave.nnThe excitement of the Ookvoot Scavenger Hunt!
Courage in the face of fury! Gratitude from the imga! nnWishing his savior a long and prosperous life.
You did it! You marvel of heroic mastery, you've saved my celebration!
Admiring Ookvoot? nnAvoiding the dangers of Elden Root?nnThe coziness of Ookvoot! The convenience of so much fruit and fish!
You sure are slow, aren't you? I'll be sure the Baron is aware of your conduct when we return. Surely any reward you would recieve will be halved by this treatment!
Y-you're alive? I can't believe it!
I have fifty merchants waiting for me to sign off on their customs papers - what makes you think your business is more important?
I know I must go home soon, but the heat is so relaxing.
I was sure we'd be safe in Koeglin Village, but I was wrong. Once my son Solon is safe, we will head to Alcaire Castle!
I did not think help would arrive. May your steps forever be blessed!
Her Grace was kind to me, no matter what the others say.nnWhy would someone murder her? Why?
I hear naught but rumors, but what I hear is not good. They say the very slaves are stricken with Blight, and Ebonheart is a den of sickness and vice.nnI only wish him to come home safely.
The <<1>> is determined to find the source of this Blight, is it not? This one respects the dedication shown.
An-Gei will help you, slave-friend. He waits outside to free us!
The Sand Cove is south of here. You can't miss it. nnBe careful down there. Those creatures have some nasty claws on them.

To think those dreugh were touching my wares at the cove! One shudders in disgust at the thought of it. nnOnce that cutlery is back in my posession, we'll need to hire servants to scrub every piece of it spotless.
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
I fight for honor, glory, and gold!
Your aura has diminished, though there is great power in it. nnI can heal your soul, if you wish.
Hoom wishes luck to the <<1>>!
Expressing the displeasure caused by Hoom's victory!nnSulking in his tent.
The intense desire for an object. The earnest request for its possession. nnWill the <<1>> be giving it to Wud?
Celebrating victory of the <<1>>.!nnPointing out the repeated failure of Hoom to win the Scavenger Hunt. nnWatching him suffer from the poisonous sting of regret.
The Razorvines are saying we have a fighting chance now. Something bad happened to the Imperials in Haven.nnI wish I knew what was going on. We never hear anything until it's all over.

My servants are gossiping about foul-smelling creatures shambling around Haven.nnI swear, these Bosmer are hopelessly rustic. If they bathed instead of waiting for it to rain on them, they'd smell fine.nnWell, they'd smell better.
Let's give you a chance to practice with your new weapon.
You are truly a blessed being, <<1>>.
You saved my son, and now you have saved all of Alcaire! Thank you, <<1>>!
There are several fire pits between here and the docks. Just send up some smoke from any of them and we'll run right down to meet you there!
Another impressive performance! The crowd loved it!
They say you saved us, <<1>>. I am grateful that you came to us in our hour of need.
Hm. Is that another delivery from Wort that I smell?
Maggots squirm through the rotted flesh of this corpse.
Maggots squirm through the rotted flesh of this corpse.
Maggots squirm through the rotted flesh of this corpse.
Our ship's the Star of the Sea. She's a small vessel, but that's why she's so quick.
Our ship's the Star of the Sea. She's a small vessel, but that's why she's so quick.
There are several fire pits between here and the docks. Just send up some smoke from any of them and we'll run right down to meet you there!
This is what I like to see - fat bugs crawling all over and chewing on garbage.nnI can't tell you how fulfilled it makes me to see vermin thrive!
My deputy, Ovis should be in the Harbormaster's office, south of the docks.  Don't expect him to be in a good mood.

Deputy Felisa has been spending a lot of time on the docks talking to sugar runners.  nnNo one knows you down there.  Follow her, and see what you can find out.nnIf she notices you, return and tell me.  Then all you can do is try again.
With the blow aginst the Imperials in Haven, do you think the Bretons be leaving soon?
You couldn't pay me enough to get me to leave the city.nnIt's dangerous in the wilds, you know.
Duke Bealton and Baron Gradwyn can rot in Oblivion. All we wanted was to be left alone.
My son's working down at Deleyn's Mill.nnThere isn't enough work in the city for everyone, it seems.
My family came to Daggerfall before the last war began.nnIt's rather nice here, don't you think?
Duke Bealton and Baron Gradwyn can rot in Oblivion. All we wanted was to be left alone.
Duke Bealton and Baron Gradwyn can rot in Oblivion. All we wanted was to be left alone.
Duke Bealton and Baron Gradwyn can rot in Oblivion. All we wanted was to be left alone.
It's very reassuring to hear the guards on patrol at night.nnI sleep a little easier knowing they're alert.
The Daggerfall Covenant means nothing to me personally. It's political jousting as far as I'm concerned. nnSo long as no one takes away my ale, the king can ally with whoever he wants.
Don't trust those foreigners. nnThey're here to take advantage of the new peace we have as part of the Daggerfall Covenant. They're like crows on the edge of a battlefield.nnSo, where ya from?
May the Divines walk with you, stranger.
I sure hope that's harpy blood.

If any of the Orlishkaarn get in your way, don't think twice about taking their lives. nnIt's bad enough they kill us slowly with their disease.nnAttacking our workers is an act of cowardice. Ashlanders have no honor.
The spirit said the Blood Thorn are involved?nnThis is grave news. Please, hurry to Wyress Jacinta at our camp to the west.
Wars keep the commoners occupied and out of mischief.
I'm not interested in politics. The subject bores me.nnWhy can't people talk about something else?nnIt's like my mother always said: "There's more to life than wars and strife."
I'm short three farmhands.nnGetting this farm up and running again is going to be a challenge.
We used to be at war with Camlorn. Now I hear they're under attack. nnServes them right!
The netch slips easily from your grip.
If the Daggerfall Covenant brings a long-lasting peace, then it obviously has Arkay's blessing.
The warrant you have gives you legal permission to enter Irano's house. nnI expect you'll run into some resistence from him.
I'm preparing our father's body for interment within the Bonebarrow.

I was just telling the Commander about my father.nnHe was a hero, Imperial. A hero. And you killed him! You or your kind. It doesn't matter.nnIs your head comfortable in my pack, Commander? Heh. Ha ha!
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it certainly isn't better.
I don't see why we let the Lion Guard stay in Daggerfall.
Once my business is finished here, I'll return to Orsinium.
There are far too many trees around Daggerfall.
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it certainly isn't better.
The food in Glenumbra leaves much to be desired.
The Lorais River sings as it passes through Daggerfall. nnListen closely, and you'll hear it.
The Julianos School is an interesting project. nnIt's still quite small, but someday, it could be a popular destination for those who would learn magic.
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it certainly isn't better.
I wish I had brought more slaves with me when I moved here.nnIt's nearly impossible to run a household with less than ten!
The stone pavement is not the most comfortable path, is it?
This one cannot find Khajitti delicacies in the local markets. Alas!
Sentinel is very different from Daggerfall. It's a city of warriors.
I keep a shrine to Ebonarm, the God of War, in my home.nnI don't know any Redguard who doesn't.
If business doesn't improve in Daggerfall, I might transfer my ships to Wayrest.
My holdings in Haarfingar are much more substantial than the ones I have here in Daggerfall.

If what you say is true, the house father's spirit will be restless. nnHe never experienced a natural death, and he was never laid to rest in a city of the dead.nnWe'll need to use ceremonial sconces to channel the requisite energy for a ritual.
Sit. Eat. I will leave soon.
You you saved my life. How can I possibly repay you?
I guess we might make it back to Haven after all.nnThough with all the Imperial troops still outside, it will be a while yet.
I guess we might make it back to Haven after all.nnThough with all the Imperial troops still outside, it will be a while yet.
Your eyes. I see her in your eyes. I beg of you, tell me what you found!
My cursed body is on the island to the west. Only when it is destroyed will my spirit be free.
The Bretons look down on us, just as they always have.
I'm anxious to return to Orsinium so I can be with my own kind.
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it is certainly isn't better.
The food in Glenumbra leaves much to be desired.
Sometimes, I feel like I'm being watched.
The Julianos School is an interesting project. It's still quite small, but someday it could be a popular destination for those who would learn magic.
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it certainly isn't better.
I wish I had brought more slaves with me when I moved here. It's nearly impossible to run a household with less than ten!
Alas, these markets don't carry Khajiiti delicacies.
Alas, this one cannot find Khajitti delicacies in the local markets.
I've never been to Sentinel. I'm told it's much better than any Breton city.
I keep a shrine to Ebonarm in my home. Every Redguard I know honors the God of War that way.
The walls are too stifling. I'm used to the freedom of the sea.
These people think their little hills are impressive. They know nothing of Skyrim's mountains.
Your aura is diminished, though there is great power in it. nnI can heal your soul, if you so desire.
I guess we'll be going out to attack the Imperials sometime soon. Seems their reinforcements were cut off or something.
We've got the Imperials on the run now.nnWell, not literally. But we've got them just where they want us!
Take that package to Sticky - he is on the road behind the Inn to the east.
We're not interested in local politics, even though rumors might claim otherwise.
We're here to offer our support to the Daggerfall Covenant.
Hammerfell is a city of warriors. When my work with the Lion Guard is complete, I plan to return there.
Is that Wood Elf... is she really going to eat that? This one wishes she could go home to Tenmar.
They're saying something about necromancy and sload going on down in Haven.nnI don't understand magic, so I don't trust it. I'll stick to cold steel. I bet that'll work just fine against sload.
I shouldn't have joined the fighting at Haven. I took an arrow in the arm. Now I'm stuck here when I should be at Thistlewhip's side.
Your contribution to the war effort has not gone unmarked, <<1>>. Should you find yourself in Elden Root, I recommend you visit the Thalmor.
We must put our differences aside and do our best to keep Tamriel safe for all its inhabitants.

Our remains lie in the urns scattered about Othrenis. nnWithin them, our spirits and our very essence are under the sway of the priestess of Othrenis.nnI know not how I broke free of her control. I must not waste this chance.
The Knights of the Dragon have always protected Daggerfall's royal family.
target: The Knights del Drago have always protected Daggerfall's royal family.

source: The king and his family are under our protection. No duty carries greater honor.
I don't know why Daggerfall isn't the capital.nnAfter all, we're in the Daggerfall Covenant, not the Wayrest Covenant.
There isn't enough action in Daggerfall to keep an old soldier like me busy.
If you venture near the docks, watch for pickpockets and petty thieves.
I've worked with Daggerfall's guards for a long time.nnThere's no other city I would rather serve.
Our guards remain vigilant, especially in these difficult times.
Please, leave me.
If you're a new recruit, I have crafting supplies and practice gear.
I am still waiting to see that ring of yours.
I am waiting to see that ring. You done yet?
You know if you want to wait I am sure I can find that soul gem.
May the Goddess of Air bring guidance to you in your journey.
You'll find Galas on a small island east of here. You might even be able to see him from the docks.
Please, just tell her I'm dead.
Have you spoken to the Foreman or Sulen the Tailor?  Sulen is here in Kragenmore, to the south of here.  You can find the Foreman somewhere on the Blightfence to the northeast.
You there! Arrest that cretin before he slithers away again, in the name of the Three!
Please, I've done nothing wrong! You have to believe me!
Soon, these people will be ready to return to their homes.
Be careful handling those samples. nnIf the Dreugh really are carrying the affliction, the disease will spread easily.
<This peasant is unconscious. Reme Hositte's magic has enthralled him.>
<This peasant is unconscious. Reme Hositte's magic has enthralled him.>
The peasant is in the thrall of Reme Hositte's magic, and unconscious.
If my mistress finds Raijo, she will be cross!
If Raijo wants his freedom, I can only give him the key to the shackles on his hands.nnIt is beyond my power to remove the shackles on my heart.
Have you spoken to my cousin?  She can usually be found in the great hall of House Dres, in eastern Kragenmore.
Hello, hello my friend.  Did you change your mind about a shirt?  Or a new cloak?  It's always such a pleasure to see you.
Now, down to business.  I have things for you to do if you are willing.
Ravnos may be good, but my magic will make sure he never gets lucky again.
I felt so loved in her arms... I must see her again.
My savior! My wondrous hero! Huff!nnOh... dear... I believe I'm about to faint.
You will find spirits all around these ruins. They cannot leave here.nnAfter you defeat them, you must use a soul cage to capture their eternal essence.

Violent deaths frequently cause the spirit to endure.nnWhile binding those spirits to service is abhorrent, the Mages Guild believes much can be learned from their knowledge.nnThen we will give the remains a proper burial.
Fire rains from the stormclouds... there is no shelter from this agony!
Mother... loves us?
To be finding Lurmpi in bestial Maleron's circus, northwest on the road to Elden Root. The pain of absence! The anxiety and fear!
Chirruk. Kik kik kik!
The gratitude for finding Lurmpi! To be hugging you - if you were properly groomed.
Tik tiki tik... chik-ik!
I've given you a list of plants I believe will work for the curative.... What was I saying?
<<1>>.  I think that is a name to remember.
We will never forget what you have done for us, <<1>>.
This is preposterous! I am Priestess Fleile's prisoner!
These shalk carapaces are very unusual, but I certainly won't turn down a  challenge!
This is Maleron's private tent. No admittance!
Fire rains from the stormclouds... there is no shelter from this agony!
The Outfitters Guild has placed a spell over this pen to allow us to kill the pigs without causing them pain.nnWe may kill for our craft, but we do not kill wantonly.
You... you came back....
Still warm....nnThese hearts will be the first of many.
Turn the slave against that monster, and make the goblins pay for this crime.
You would have made a fine Knight of the Dragon.
target: You would have made a fine Knight del Drago.

source: What evils have you wrought, stranger? What has befallen my dear Toves?
Have you seen any sign of my love, my Arynia? I will not leave until I find her!
That is what I call commitment! I can get on board with someone like you.nnI hope the Prince doesn't need me just yet. I've got some cleaning up to do.
Please, I've done nothing to you.
I appreciate your concern for my well being, but I think I'm better off in here with my Kwama, thank you.
What are you doing? Kill them!
That toad reeks of corpses. Whatever pit you dug it from, kindly put it back.

That one should flee elsewhere. Only trouble will come to Mount Thendr now. nnThis one will keep an eye for any who may approach this way. They will not have an easy fight if they wish to rid me from this mountain.
What happened to that poor fellow?
We must put our differences aside and do our best to keep Tamriel safe for all its inhabitants.
This matter is settled. nnLeave me be.
What is this fine <<1>> carrying, Belec? It appears you've got a treat.
I trust you are enjoying the show?nnAnd have you tried the honey cake at our concession tent? It's quite sinful.
Oh, my poor Senche. What have they done to you?nnThere, there, my friend. We'll get you fixed up soon.
You made it? I'm so glad. Has the fighting started yet?
Have you seen any sign of my love, my Arynia? I will not leave until I find her!
Mrow.
You have my word, <<1>>. All that I know, so shall the Queen and her Thalmor know. There was never a truer soul than Excellent Ervas.
Scavengers and vagrants want to capitalize on the chaos here. nnIf they get in your way, feel free to punish them as you see fit.
All the guar-herders of the Kagesh know of your deeds. nnOur tribe is grateful. The gates of our village are open to you.
What have you found?
The smoke is sweet incense on the wind. I'll fight until my last breath just to see their stricken faces when those damned merchants return.
<<1>> won't let me near the entrance to Necris. nnShe claims it's too dangerous, but how dangerous can a bunch of disgruntled spirits be? nnShe looks at me as if I were some common graverobber!
I can guess from the shovel you're carrying that my fool of a son sent you. nnLet's talk for a bit before you start performing meaningless labor.
Ha! He must have been surprised. Always was a gullible boy, my son.
Thooth thind bug. Bug thing tongue. nnThooth thad now. Thill hungry.
Not wanting Yoon to be harmed. nnSaying he is pleased to hear Yoon is okay.
What would possess me to attack my friend? In truth, I don't even remember what began our quarrel.
I feel quite foolish for being angry at my friend, for no good reason! Perhaps I'd been out in the sun too long...
Our guards remain vigilant, especially in these difficult times.
The sooner we get out of here, the better!
Dig for bones. Bring me bones.
Thank goodness you're back! Did you find Gads?
You think I'd talk to you after you turned me in? You'd better get out of my face.
It's a good thing there's law-abiding citizens like you to report these events when they are found.
You see now how I recognized you when you entered my tomb. We have met in the First Age.nnIt is good to see you again, my friend.
Leave me be! You have your cures, now go!
Did you have any problems getting what I asked for? nnPlease be careful. I wouldn't want you to get in trouble!
I just watched an Imperial soldier dragged into Barkbite. As much flailing as he was doing, I thought I would hear him screaming.nnIn Barkbite, they bite your bark... that hurt me speak aloud.
I did not call upon you, Imperial.
The hostages are being sacrificed inside the temple. If you bring them to me, I will take care of getting them to safety.
Have you come here to save me?
Take care in Senie. What was once a prosperous town is little more than ruins now.
You are welcome here, Clanfriend. May your kills be quick and many.
Andalii says my faith will shield me from the Blight, but even she knows that is the one disease we cannot cure! If I was to catch it, I would be forced to leave the temple, or worse...
Are you from the temple? When will we be seen?!
Are you from the temple? When will we be seen?!
Are you from the temple? When will we be seen?!
Meep meep!
You spoke to a wolf? What are you on about?
While I'm under this curse and trapped in this form, I cannot have the revenge on Hircine I so desperately desire. My only hope for vengeance lies with you, <<1>>.

My sister resides in the sanatorium before you. I believe her suite was in the main building. I'm afraid I can't identify her anymore, so far gone as she is.nnI will not question your methods on obtaining the key. I know what must be done.
The Tribunal does not tolerate lawbreakers, no matter what their rationale may be.nnSmugglers bring goods into Davon's Watch. We must cut them off at the source.nnThat source is Emberquay.
How could I have been so blind? If the others hear of my hubris, I am certain to be punished!
I will stay here now and atone for what I almost did. Though not of my free will, my actions could have harmed many others.nnI will use my skill to heal those are suffering.
You need not worry about what is in the bag. It is better if it simply disappears, and we can all continue our normal lives.nnAnd please don't mention any of this to Jivon. He would not understand.
I am penniless and alone, and now the only things I hold dear are all gone!nnPlease, you are the only one who has shown even a bit of concern for me.
Go!  Find the tongue of the Argonian.  Bring it to me.
This Magis Order Nightblade took his own life. His body shows the first stages of lycanthropy.
Bless you, <<1>>. I don't know what we'd have done if you hadn't found us.

You can stop annihilating those unfortunate ghosts now. The prismatic projectors are fully functional again. I wasn't sure if I could realign the expurgated energies, but then I remembered the phasing crystals could be offset to... oh.nnNever mind.
We've already helped several survivors through the portal. Your efforts, I assume?
Get a drop of the purple potion, a pinch of reagent and then combine them with the bergamont seeds in the alchemy set.
Under sun and sky, Clanfriend.
If you're looking for the innkeeper, she's to the southwest.  You can find the jeweler in her shop to the south.
We have seen many tribes rot from the noble houses' corruption.nnOne day, the Nerevarine will avenge the lost. He will punish the Tribunal for its heresy!
Blessings of the ancestors upon you, Clanfriend.
House Dres loyal, that's my new pledge.  I buy only from them.  So should we all.
I meant what I said.  You're no longer welcome here.  Do your business and get out.
If we are to support House Dres, then that's what I suppose we will do.  Long live House Dres...
We may have lost our homes, but we have our lives.
We may have lost our homes, but we have our lives.
We may have lost our homes, but we have our lives.
We may have lost our homes, but we have our lives.
We may have lost our homes, but we have our lives.
Though these people have lost much, they have each other. One day Camlorn will be theirs again.
Have you found any unblighted alit? nnThey're all around this valley. nnIf you can charm them, bring them back to me.
Noldres gave you a note? Please, friend, let me see it.
The stench of daedric corruption is dissipating.
You can hunt the tarn snakes around here for the meat I need.
Master Drathal is waiting for the jelly. Bring it to him as fast as you can!nnI need to bandage myself up before I head back...
We must attend to other duties for now. nnOnce you've recieved the information we need, come back to us here. nnThen we'll discuss our next step.
Just be glad you're not the fiend we're seeking.
The stench of blight is fading - I can sense the Elden Tree stirring in the soil.
The Lion Guard must remain vigilant, especially in these changing times.
A good batch... a good batch indeed! The comberry scent truly comes through!
By the end of a shift, I'm ready for a flagon of ale.
By the end of a shift, I'm ready for a flagon of ale.
You couldn't pay me enough to leave the city. nnIt's dangerous in the wilds, you know.
My forebears came to Wayrest before the last war began. nnIt's rather nice here, don't you think?
The Daggerfall Covenant means nothing to me. It's political jousting, as far as I'm concerned. nnSo long as no one takes away my ale, the king can ally with whoever he wants.
I haven't heard from my sister in Alcaire for some time now. She used to send letters regularly. nnWhat do you think happened out there?
Don't trust any of those foreigners. They're here to take advantage of our peace and prosperity.nnEveryone in the Daggerfall Covenant made sacrifices. Those foreigners all benefit from that.
I'm sure Wayrest will return to normal soon enough.
I'm not used to seeing so many others here. Redguards, Dunmer, Khajiit.nnNext thing you know, they'll be letting in Argonians!
If the Daggerfall Covenant brings a long-lasting peace, then it would seem to have Arkay's blessings.
Aren't you <<1>>? I've heard of you! nnIt's an honor to make your acquaintance.
I must speak to my maid about how poorly she cleans our clothing.
Wayrest is a fine city, but it's not Orsinium.
Wayrest is not what I expected it to be. nnFor a start, it's a lot less backwards than I thought it would be.
I'm not impressed with Wayrest. nnIt's crowded and filthy, as most Breton cities are.
Stormhaven is a good name for this place. It rains nearly every day!
I don't remember much about the past few days. It's all a blur. nnMy head aches something fierce now. I must have been at death's door.
What are you looking at, traveller? nnDidn't you expect to see Dunmer in Wayrest these days?
I wish I had brought more slaves with me when I moved here.nnIt's nearly impossible to run a household with less than ten!
This stone pavement isn't the most comfortable path you've trod, is it?
Alas! This one cannot find Khajiiti delicacies in the local markets!
Unlike Wayrest, Hammerfell is a city of warriors.
I keep a shrine to Ebonarm, the God of War, in my home. nnI don't know any Redguard who doesn't!
Each passing day the Daggerfall Covenant exists, my family's trade business improves.
My holdings in Haarfingar are much more substantial than my pitiful properties in Daggerfall.
The Bretons look down on us, as they always have.
I'm anxious to return to Orsinium so I can be with my own people.nnThey don't want my kind around here.
Wayrest is bigger than Daggerfall, but it certainly is not better.
The food in Stormhaven leaves much to be desired.
Sometimes, I feel as though I'm being watched.
I can't wait to get back to Valenwood. nnBeing in Wayrest is like being imprisoned. So many walls!
The Red Mountain has been trembling for a long time.nnWe're unsure when it will settle again.
I should have brought some slaves with me when I moved here.
Alas, the markets don't carry Khajiiti delicacies.
Alas! This one cannot find Khajiiti delicacies in the local markets!
Sentinel is better than any Breton city. nnMy heart will rejoice when I can finally return to Hammerfell.
I keep a shrine to Ebonarm, the God of War, in my home. nnI don't know any Redguards who don't.
The walls are too stifling for a hero like me. nnI'm used to the freedom of the sea.
These people think their little hills are impressive. nnThey know nothing of Skyrim's mountains!
See how the remembrance crystal glows? That means you've saved many innocents from an unthinkable fate.
I hope your search proves successful.

I thought of a joke while you were gone. Why do Wood Orcs cut down trees? Because they hate things smarter than them.nnNo, huh?nnI've been out here alone for weeks. You want real comedy, see if you can dig up Shadowhiskers. People tell me he's funny.
I was afflicted before we even reached Stonefalls. I'd hoped the Houses had found a cure for the Blight, but our cries fall on deaf ears.
Praise the gods, you've made it back in one piece!nnEach day I prayed to Mara, asking her to keep you safe from harm.
Enter freely, but mind your manners.nnSee the crack in rocks behind me? nnWith the instructions I gave you, you should be able slip through and meet <<1>>.
Leave me alone.nnI've got nothing for you!
Please don't hurt me! It was all his idea!
Destroy the focus crystals! I can't move while this binding spell holds me.
I don't know anything!
I just want to start over.nnThat's all.
We are not interested in the local politics, though rumors say otherwise.
The Bloodthorns are holding the Duke in the lighthouse. You'll have to fight your way in there if you really plan to rescue him.
Chirruk. Kik kik kik!
Go on, go on. I have another bott- hic! - I have this thing. That I have to do.
Why are you standing here? Get back to your... oh! I beg your pardon!nnDid Lord Averos send you to train the new recruits?
Ahji thanks you for your help, and this one sincerely hopes you are not torn apart by wraiths.
Some Bretons look down on the Orcs, but it's fair to say some of us look down on them.
Some Orcs want to return to the days when we ruled these lands. nnI'm not one of them. My life is comfortable enough.
They look down upon others, the Bretons do, although they aren't as bad as some. nnAt least Bretons understand what being enslaved is really like.
You aren't looking for skooma, are you? nnThis one does not buy or sell such goods.
I have as much right to live in Wayrest as any Breton does.
May Ebonarm walk beside you in battle, traveller.
The Dominion has strengthened Valenwood, Summerset, and Elsweyr. Some Bosmer ignore the treaty and hold old grudges.
I have learned as much as I can and I must head off to the Siege Camp.nnYou should talk to Magus Commander Danain at the Siege Camp when you are finished here.

Thanks to you, my wife's sacrifice was not in vain. nnAs I teach my child about the mother she'll never know, I'll tell her about you.nnYou've done a great service to all of us who live in the forest.
When I report back to Mournhold, I'll tell the Three of your valiant deeds here.nnUntil then, may the Three bless you and keep you.
Consider yourself fortunate. You are not the fiend we seek.
You're back?
The Daggerfall Covenant will bring peace and prosperity to all of Tamriel.
You'd be surprised how many Lion Guard soldiers are already scattered throughout Tamriel.
I've gained a bit of weight since coming to Wayrest. Oddest thing ever! nnI don't remember eating that much. Maybe I've had more than my share now and then.
House Dres thought this Blight was nothing more than the product of disgruntled Ashlanders.nnI tried to convince House Redoran of this folly, but never discovered the true source.
You can find sulphuric gems all around the pools here.  Be careful of the shalk.
I'm ready to train you for the tasks ahead of you.
What can I teach you about being a mage, my friend?
What would you like to learn, my friend?
How can I help you today, my friend?
We can speak discreetly about what you need to learn.
You are here to learn, are you not?
What do you need to learn today, my friend?
You will need utmost concentration to study with me. nnIf you'e ready, we can begin.
So you wish to learn more, do you? I can assist you.
What would you like to know, my friend?
This is so embarrassing.
One color stains the nightmares of the wicked.nnRed.
Ah, clean water. It's so easy to take these little things for granted, don't you think?

Through you, I found Father Montague' s magical beacon and linked it to my own. I felt six pass over. I believe that's all of them.nnI must rest after such powerful magic, but they are safe thanks to you. Look for them on the ridge above my tent.

Through you, I found Father Montague' s magical beacon and linked it to my own. I felt six pass over. I believe that's all of them.nnI must rest after such powerful magic, but they are safe thanks to you. Look for them on the ridge above my tent.

Through you, I found Father Montague' s magical beacon and linked it to my own. I felt six pass over. I believe that's all of them.nnI must rest after such powerful magic, but they are safe thanks to you. Look for them on the ridge above my tent.
Go, there's no time to waste. I'll make my way back to Tilmo's camp. Go on!
Those cursed grave robbers are disturbing our honored dead. nnSomething must be done. Someone must stop them.
Be wary of looters. nnIf we weren't stretched so thin between this disease and the disaster at Senie, we'd have taken care of them a long time ago.
You're a brave one, to venture into those pools, between the shalk and the snakes.  There's plenty of gems to be had in their midst; just head to the southeast and you won't miss them.
The vipers you need for the venom are in the Sulphuric Pools area to the southeastst of here.  Just use that vial I gave you to collect the venom, and be careful of their reaction!
Is it true that you killed the Kwama Queen and destroyed the nests?  This means we can get back to work
target: I never thought I would see it happen.  Thank you!

source: Have you found any eggs yet?  You can find them inside the mine to the northwest.  They may be in nests or in safe corners.  You can also get them from the kwama sometimes.
With the queen dead and the nests gone, we can finally get back to work.  You saved us a lot of lost wages, never mind the danger.
Lluthyne's holed up in the house west of here. nnShe's too stubborn to see this place is a lost cause!
Look who it is... again. As I said, you can speak to Warden Moreau. He might offer you something if you mention his assistance with my endeavors. He'll know what I mean.
You'll find <<1>> north of here. He went to go look at the farms outside Camlorn.
Mazte is cheap, and it doesn't age well. Especially when aging in the bottom of a netch's stable.
Have you found the source of the corruption? Look for anything out of the ordinary.
The netchling's tentacles are tangled around the fulcrum of the windmill. There's no way to loosen them without some kind of lubricant.
Find Nedao, and you will find the key to my bonds.
It was glorious to feel Blacksap bones crack under my fists again!
I feel my lifeblood swiftly leaving me. Give me strength to witness the last of these vile abominations fall to justice!
That is odd.nnI feel as if someone is watching me all of a sudden. Perhaps I should leave this place sooner rather than later.nnI wouldn't want to pick up any lost spirits now.
Use the pot to coat yourself in Moondrop Musk - then run up the ramp! A Thunderbug will chase you - lure it into the Saproot Snares along the ramps.
Rathell lies within his tomb, sealed to all but a select few. I stole the key from one of my mentors before I alerted the Ordinators to our hubris.
The blighted kwamherds are down there in the ravine to the northwest and in the mine itself to the west.  Kill as many as you can.
Are you going into the tarn? Be careful not to drink any of the water.
Take heed when traveling. There is corruption all over the land.
Curse these wounds, that Ihdana is not able to help you.  Have you found any tools?  The mine entrance is to the northeast.
Our triumph in Camlorn will be remembered for years to come.
Our triumph in Camlorn will be remembered for years to come.
Our triumph in Camlorn will be remembered for years to come.
Our triumph in Camlorn will be remembered for years to come.
You say some hooded fool accosted you? Well, better you than me, I say.
Soon, when the sick are healed, we'll return to Camlorn and make a new city from the ashes of the old.
Hopefully the Ordinators will be able to find some use for the information we gathered here. I can only hope the suffering we caused was not in vain.

My sister, Kireth, also seeks relics from Dwemer ruins throughout the land. nnIf you come across her, do tell her I wish her luck.nnI know the next time I see her, iit will be inside the venerated halls of the Mages Guild!
I've hunted with Shaali hundreds of times. Now she gives her praise to you instead.nnTrouble my eyes no more, s'wit.
Have you spoken to our guar herdsmen? They have been troubled by nix-hounds in recent weeks. Aiding them would surely open the hearts of all Kagesh to you.
Please, share with me the knowledge you bring.
Oh, I forgot to mention one thing before you left.nnI might have... possibly... maybe... dropped the talisman before I gave it to you. nnI'm sure it's fine, though. Right? Right.
Praise Arkay! Those wolves are gone!
I have been unlucky as of late. It seems I am thoroughly broke.
The Dunmer stored weapons all over the fort.  In particular the largest fort building to the east should have many to collect.
Thanks for the food... is there something else you need? I know my fellow Jaqspur would appreciate getting their rations sooner rather than later.
Are you from Daen Seeth? Have you any news of the conclave?
The werewolves are gone? What do we do now? Rebuild? nnHow will we pay for it all?

Our Houses hold no love for each other, yet Bravosi insists we unite against the Ashlanders. I wonder his motivesnnYou must be the stranger everyone is whispering about. What can House Redoran do for you in these trying times?

You can find mucksponge growing near the poorer houses in the northern district. Discriminating gardeners weed it out.nnBy the way, the mazte here is far too rich. If you can salvage some bottles from the vacated houses as well, that would be ideal.

To soar like the Jaqspur, you must search the treetops for branches infused with Pact-Magic. Use the Boughdancer scroll upon the enchanted bough, and it will pull you into its arms.nnAfter you've dropped off the rations, drop by the Eledrim camp.
Do not try to save me! I want to... be with Andre....nnPlease, all I ask is that you take his ashes to the Old Stone Bridge for me. Please.
Is that my coin purse?
Hey now, take it easy! What do you want?

The witch lives north of Aldcroft. You can follow the road, but once you reach the swamp, you'll need to look for torches lighting the way.nnIf you could hurry, that would be most appreciated. nnTrust me. You never want to be in debt to a witch.
Barnabe sent you, did he? Fool never could shut his mouth.
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
Have you found any weapons we can use? If not, I may just fight off the soldiers with my bare hands. Ah, brings back fond memories!
<<1>> and Vusara were both promising in their potential. nnIt's a shame to see them disregard what they've pledged to uphold.
I can sense the magic already. nnYou were successful were you not?
I do hope the tonic helped you?
The ship leaves port tonight. They will surely founder on the rocks without the ligthhouse to guide them, and this monster will regain his ill-gotten slaves!
Be careful. The enemy could march past this tower at any moment.
It could butcher an army and never slow. There's no way to stop it.
Use the scroll at the Summoning Site. From what I can tell of the horror's path, the site should be to the west.
The horn you brought me called in many wars against our neighbors. Maybe it should again.nnThe people here think I'm a decent with a bow. The Dominion could probably use me.
Thank you for bringing me grandmama. You're a good sort.nnBut don't believe what the others here told you! I'm not that grateful.
To be honest, I'm leery of searching around this place. I don't want to touch anything - I could catch some vile disease!
My dear, I have heard the commotion from the village. I beg you be blunt - tell me what has become of <<1>>!
For her sake, please disregard Alena's ramblings. nnShe can be quite excitable, and I wouldn't want her to hurt herself.
I was a fool, pure and simple. Curse his eyes!
The tapestry you brought me was woven many ages ago by my foremothers. It would have been irreplaceable.
We've lost so much,,,,
Whatever's happened to us is nothing compared to what's happening up on Gil-Var-Delle.
I keep reminding myself that I'm lucky to be alive and safe in here.

I used to think the Blacksap were kind of all right. They were different, but you could talk to them.nnWhen they attacked Brukbrook, one of them came into my hut waving an axe, yelling that traitors should die.

You may wonder why I'm trying to run a store in a refugee camp. I have a long-term plan.nnStep one, I buy whatever anyone wants to sell. Step two, I wait for the Aldmeri Dominion to liberate Brukbrook. Step three, profit!
You dare come back without my rum?  Go on over to Valmori's ship.  It's just north of here.
You will find sick people throughout the town of Ebonheart.  The Blight spreads quickly.
I'm going to the Quarantine Master presently.  I just need to pack my things...
I'm going to the Quarantine Master presently.  I just need to pack my things...
I'm going to the Quarantine Master presently.  I just need to pack my things...
I'm going to the Quarantine Master presently.  I just need to pack my things...
I'm on my way to the Quarantine Master.  I just need to pack a few things...
I'm on my way to the Quarantine Master.  I just need to pack a few things...
To think skooma has played such an indirect role in my life.nnI curse its very creation.
You've got no evidence against me! You keep your mouth shut, or I'll make you regret it!
You are back. Alive! A surprise for me, I admit it. Dare I ask... did you do the deed...?
It's a simple plan. It should work perfectly, but I can't do it myself. nn<<1>> would immediately know it was me. nnI need someone else to execute it, so she won't suspect I'm involved.
Sugar takes good care of us.
What?  Are you afraid to lick a Hist Tree?  Even little Argonians are not afraid.  Go on, it is just there.
Loosen the rope from this pole quickly and I'll run back to Aldcroft on my own.
It's difficult to stay awake, but I can't fall asleep. I won't surrender my mind to the Huntress.
Please free my fellow villagers. nnEither break the cages or use the keys that the guards carry.
The cliff racers are all over this mountain. nnI can't wait to be rid of the foul things. nnPersonally, I think <<1>> enjoys telling me to scrub their filth from the temple walkways.
Any luck tracking down the spy?
Take the Lifetimber Flowers and plant them in the Blighted Gnarls and the Pestilent Root within Black Log. Use the tunnel to Gil-Var-Delle to the east to reach Black Log.
You've done this town a great service. Now I must do the same with the mort flesh you've given me.
I can imagine what <<1>> will say. My situation is hopeless.nnPerhaps I'm doomed to a life of solitude.nnThe Almsivi are deaf to my prayers.
It's worse than I thought in there, isn't it? You seem to be mostly unharmed; for this I am grateful. Innocent blood on my hands over a simple favor would haunt me for days on end.

I'll need to recalibrate these critters and of course re-examine my use of this enchant. nnI do wonder if that was perhaps the cause of our camp fire we had that one evening... I suppose that is more likely than a pack of wild Alits with fire breath.
Ah, my dear, brave champion. You have slain Hircine's Aspect in fair combat, and for this I cannot fault you.nnWhatever treasure you find within the Bear is yours, and well-earned.
You'll find the entrance to the gauntlet just behind me. If you survive and slay Goreclaw and alarm will be raised. We will escape in the resulting chaos.
The Huntress has fled, and you have taken possession of Hircine's Third Stone. This is unthinkable! Had I not seen it with my own eyes...
I can't believe Briran thinks to cut me out of our partnership, despite the fact that I was the one to acquire the kwama eggs at such a low price!
Unfortunately, I can't just kill the gaoler. nnI'd love to leave this place with a trail of blood behind me, but that would just makes me easier to find.
I'm sorry, but you should speak to my husband. nnThis cough makes it hard for me to think clearly.
Heimlyn Keep is up this path. nnStay right at the fork. You can't miss it.
I may have cheated death today, but I know it's coming! Perhaps I'll hire a few bodyguards... but they could be bribed to kill me as well!nnOh, curse my fate!
Silvenar.nnI am honored you would speak with me again.
I saw a few dogs running north. The Huntress will hear of Goreclaw's demise and know to expect a dangerous opponent.
When I was a child, I used to gather all kinds of kwama cuttle. nnIt's an incredibly versatile substance. You can craft with it, you can eat it, and it has a wonderful smell when it's roasted!
I will not tolerate stealing, no matter the reason. If they were in desperate need, perhaps they should have turned to the Houses they have lived under for so long!
Best keep your eye on your purse if you plan on loitering about the docks. With the shipyard closed, there's naught for those thugs to do except make trouble.
Best keep your eye on your purse if you plan on loitering about the docks. With the shipyard closed, there's naught for those thugs to do except make trouble.
You must hurry! We've already fallen behind the caravan and I fear if they move ahead without us, we'll be nothing but easy pickings for bandits!
By the Three, you smell awful. nnI'll take that as a sign of your success.
Move on, meat. I'm getting hungry.
You won't have any luck soothing my angered ancestors.nnTry the families who have awakened, but not attacked you.nnThey're all around the tomb.
Excuse me. I'm dealing with something of a crisis at the moment.
The Solir Nath ancestral tombs are southeast of here.nnI left most of my things down in the tombs.nnBe careful!
The spirits have calmed but their bickering only strengthens. There is no hope... no hope for either of them. They are both so very young... why must it end like this? Why!?
I am unbound. I hear the Wild singing, feel it flowing through the land. Balance has been restored.
The spirits have calmed but their bickering only strengthens. There is no hope... no hope for either of them. They are both so very young... why must it end like this? Why!?
I buried our family's treasures in the fields. I also hid some heirlooms inside large chests in the houses to the west.nnBe careful. The trackers are being followed by their loyal pets.
Thank you for returning my necklace to me.nnI have lost many things when the Red Rooks took over our farms but at least I still have my son and a token of the love a man once had for me.
Be careful.nnMy specialities lie in dealing with the undead, but I'm no match for the acolytes guarding the focus.
Her eyes... I felt so calm next to her.
You are the most honored guests at my party, <<1>>. The invaders may return, but with you here we are safe - and have an excellent show to boot!
It's good to see you, <<1>>. The guests have been telling stories about you for quite some time now.
I'd go myself, but, well... knife in the back. Oh, and could you keep this between us?nnI don't want anyone else finding out where Blanche is. She's been through enough.
There are Imperial Supply crates all over the beaches to the west. Just use that Kindlepitch I gave you on a few of them.
Slay the Swamp Spirit roaming this swamp.
Thanks for the severed head, <<1>>. If our rations run out, it should come in handy.

I'll head out of here shortly. nnI still don't know why the Orcs were mining pyroil stone. I'd like to find out.nnI think you should head east. I've heard there's trouble in Haven. They could use someone like you.
Take care if you venture out on the plain. All manner of unnatural beasts there.
I will do anything I can to stop this darkness from spreading beyond Crestshade.nnFind my skull so that I can use it as a focus for my energy.
Thank you. Now my brother and I can rest peacefully.
Thank you for helping us.
Will the <<1>> be helping?nnCarefully climbing down to the ledges below.nnGathering delicious amberberries for Tung!
I don't have... much time. But you gave me something to... smile about.nnGo on.... Leave me.
The joy of a triumphant return!
Hoping Elder Brump is safe. nnRemembering the elder was seen to the south, near Stumptown.nnTelling a hero who can save him!
Praising the <<1>> for rescuing Elder Brump!
Speaking of the hero who rescued Elder Brump. nnWelcome the hero to Cliffvoot, a gem atop the hill! nnThe joyous anticipation of Elder Brump, who waits in the cave by the waterfall!
Tokutu, <<1>>! nnChewing on fat meat bugs!nnDrinking too much amberberry wine!nnNot worrying about the consequences tomorrow!
Thinking the <<<LOCAL_PLAYER_RACE>> would be a fine sentry for Cliffvoot.

Ah! An adventurer! Always so inspiring to have someone like you around town. I had hoped my son Martin would take up an exciting profession like that, but I'm beginning to think the poor boy just doesn't have it in him.nnHe worries me sick, you know.
Thinking the <<<LOCAL_PLAYER_RACE>> would be a fine sentry for Cliffvoot.
Stupid arm. I hope the healers in Oldgate can do something with it.nnWhat will I do if they can't?
No longer craving the delicious taste of Amberberry Wine. nnPreferring to just drink water... and live longer.
I can't leave my Mages Guild escorts unguarded, and Blade-Turner would never forgive me if I did. I hope you find him alive.
I pray you wield my weapon well.
I'll rest easier knowing that thing isn't going to come upon us in the night and make us scream like that Black Hand captive.
You have my thanks, friend. nnMy assistant and I will now leave these detestable ruins, so I may continue my studies in earnest.
The painting was created by a talented artist who once lived in Merovec's Folly. With any luck, the painting is still in good shape after all these years.
<<1>> is wanting to share a Meat Grub with Yaab?
You've returned. I did not expect this. Dare I hope, though? Do you know the means by which I might be released?
Please don't worry about me. The priest will make sure I'm all right.nnPlease hurry to my uncle, <<1>>.
Did you find Willem? Did you get my shovel? nnThere are bloodfiends everywhere around this village. He's got to be one of them. He's probably the one with the shovel.
Please read the rune-etched stones strewn around the ruins.nnAs you learn their history, you will unbind them from this site.
Be mindful of our leafy neighbors.nnI would feel regret if any of the spriggans were harmed.
If your flash crystal's empty, then you gave better than you got.
Please find my leader, Magus Commander Bieller. He needs your help.
Please. Open the cage. Let me out!
I never wanted to serve in Ranser's army. I had a family and a farm to tend, but he conscripted every able man and woman who could hold a sword.
Your hands are too clean. You're not from around here.
Outlanders bring trouble with them. Look at what happened to the Spriggans.
My mind is much clearer now! I must make haste to Aldcroft!
Wonderful! You're alive! nnAnd you've got the totem! Even better!
You're one of those... what do they call them... Dominioners?nnDon't think you can come here and tell us how to live. You can't.
I've killed a lot of bandits looking for Leia. nnMy men are getting restless here. They need my leadership. nnPlease find her. One of the bandits around the camp here has her. I'm sure of it.
You've done well, stranger. nnYou're welcome to stay in Mireblossom as long as you like.nnConsider yourself a member of the tribe!
Have you thrashed her wayward young? nnHave you beaten them until their little legs stopped twitching?  nnNo? Then go. They are all around this tower. Show them her wrath.
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? nnI can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? nnI can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? nnI can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? nnI can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? nnI can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
<<1>>, I'll name my firstboarn child after you!
<<1>>, I'll name my firstborn child after you.
<<1>>, I'll name my firstborn after you.
<<1>>, I will name my firstborn child after you.
Please don't keep my mistress waiting. As for the Werereaver, it's not leaving my hand until Faolchu's dead.
Pelts! Look at all these pelts.nnI stabbed wolves... with my sword. Where is my sword?nnNow Gaelle will be warm. Yes!

Thank you! With your help, we'll be able to stay here much longer.nnMy husband may be dimwitted, but he's a good man. Would you mind if I tricked him into thinking he got the pelts himself? He's so drunk, he won't know the difference.
Have you found Jayne yet? I'm really worried about her.
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Who are you? What happened here? Did I do this? I can't remember. I can't remember. Please, tell me I didn't do this!
Thanks for letting me out, I've been in there so long that I'm finding it hard to move about.
Crosswych will grow and prosper once we've cleared the undead from our mine.nnI can't wait to go back to work.

Please, bring back our foals. If you have an apple, they'll follow you.nnI know apples are hard to come by these days, but <<1>> always has them for sale. You'll find her in one of the caves in the village.
Thank you again for saving me. If you had not show up I believe I would have been transformed into one of those horrid monsters in the cave.

Those dirty little thieves can be found all along the northern end of the beach. nnDidn't you know? Mudcrabs love ale. Look for one, and you'll find the other.nnIt's strange how I crashed. That little stretch of land came out of nowhere....
No time for talk - kill that thing!
You can harvest plenty of resilient sinew from the harpies around Merovec's Folly. They seem to have taken a liking to the old ruins.
Please, help me escape this awful place!
The trinkets you recovered will make delightful trophies once I find a place to settle down.
We owe you our lives. Thank you for all you've done! nnNow we have to take what you've given us and make new lives for ourselves.
Each passing generation strengthens my bond with my children and my people.nnThe foals and children grow together as one. I will protect them with every fiber of my being.
Piers is trapped closer to the mine's entrance. Raoul went further in. He may be in either the Western or Eastern End by now.
Both Isaura and Raoul went further into the mine.
Isaura and Piers did not follow me this far into the mine. If you find them alive, they'll be closer to the mine's entrance.
What are you doing out here?

The mine collapsed suddenly, just before the undead arrived. nnWe've cleared out the undead time and again, only to have them return.nnI'm more worried about the supports in the tunnels. Without the tunnels, we can't get to the ore.
Just follow this path to Merovec's Folly.nnYou'll see the <<1>> we need by its bright glow. When you collect all of it bring it to <<2>> to the west of the Lion Guard Redoubt.
The delight of freedom! nnThe hammering thumping of Brump's heart!
Please, help me escape this awful place!
You must enter the Augurium before me! nnYou must speak with my future self and bring me news of my fate.
Have you found Chaliene? The bandit's camp is to the northwest. Please hurry!
I know not where the latch is hidden, friend. nnI would check around these rocks. It must be close in order to hold these chains. Possibly near or in the rock itself?
You should search the cave and free the captives. I'd help you, but I'm still recovering from my last attempt to free them.
You'll find the highwaymen east of here. Those ruffians must have taken my supplies further into Cambray Pass.
I'm sure the bandits kidnapped Therese.nnShe's in one of their camps. There's one to the northeast and one to the northwest.
If only we could get these birds gathered up, we could be on our way, out of this dangerous place!
My fiance sent you, didn't he?
Were you able to track down the bone colossus?

The Altmer woman hired me to guide her to those ruins in the jungle.nnShe better still pay me. When we made this deal, she never said "Oh, and I don't have to pay you if Imperials invade and we're all run out of Haven."
You're right about me. I'm a no-good thief.
At last! A visitor! nnHave you had the opportunity to marvel at my creations?
I'm not quite sure how I can right my wrongs. Perhaps I should devote myself to one of the gods.nnMaybe I should make a pilgrimage to the Wayshrine of Arkay after I serve my time in jail.
Maybe folks will have extra coin to spare now that that Reachmage is gone.
The Daedra have cleared out of the manorwhat's left of it. I assume we have you to thank for that.
I just know the Razorvine hunters are going to come back carrying something disgusting, like a Thunderbug or a Khajiit.
Did you kill the Reachmage?
They say you killed Angof, the Reachmage.nnThat means the roads will soon clearn and I can move to Daggerfall to ply my trade there.
I can't stand this shadow existence, this purgatory. Please help me.
<The spirit bows its head to you in thanks.>
The spirit points at the nearby remains.
<<1>> went to Branglebracken, the dense thicket across the river to the east. Please go bring her back for me!
Why... hello. Pleased to meet you. And thank you for helping my old mother. As you can see, though, there was nothing to worry about.
Do you see anything you like? We're having a sale. Buy any dessert, get a mug of rotmeth free!
Haha! What a sight to see! You've done well, soldier.
Now it's time to get this place back in order.
You're very brave! I have hope now, thanks to you.
Maybe now, we can make a home here!
I can't thank you enough.
You're really quite brave! nnNow we can begin to rebuild our lives.
What do you have there? Let me see.
You have to unlock this cage... before I can show you anything.
I see it in your eyes... it must be done. You have cleansed the Tharn filth from the temple, yes?
Go to the library, quick as you can. We must stop Attelus!nnThe library is to the northeast.
Waste no time, friend. Attelus Tharn is on his way to the Elden Seed even now. Go!  His resting place is to the south of here.
Once, I caught Denthis trying to make nix-hounds glow purple. Why would anyone do that?
Vivec take my brother! He ran off behind this building chanting "Eyes of Akatosh" over and over.

So that thing the Imperials were building in Haven got destroyed, eh?nnYou suppose the rubble is worth anything? Maybe I could sell it to the Colovians. You know, a memento of their "trying ordeal."nnYeah, sorry. I can't say that without laughing.
We'll raise this child together as a family. nnA curse on anyone who would hold hatred against us for doing what's in our hearts!nnThank you again. It's good to know someone cares and understands.
I hope the mammoths enjoy the cake. I added all sorts of grass and a little bit of jam to it. nnLoane says I'm being foolish, but I think it'll work.
Leaftower in the hands of outsiders. I never thought I'd see the day.
I never imagined the Feladrim would jump in bed with the Imperials. Now look where we are.
If the Keeper puts his trust in you, so to shall we.
Holy water blessed by Arkay and garlic are all I need to make sure the undead won't come near my land. nnHave you found everything yet?

You're a brave soul to do this, friend. My family is in your debt.nnWe take each of the offerings to a particular shrine that symbolizes the blessings we want to receive. At least, that's what the elder tells us.
Whatever has driven these spirits into a frenzy has destroyed their souls. nnI can only pray for them.
The spirits cry out for vengeance. Appeasing them will take time. nnGo to your people and let them know we understand.
You should report to Godrun gro-Murtag, the Murtag Clan leader. We don't like strangers wandering around our battlefield.
That almost wasn't as fun as I expected it to be. Thank you for coming after me.
<<1>> doesn't understand <<2>> like I do. That's why he's so angry all the time.
Linque's transgressions cannot be forgiven. She is a danger to the community and herself.
My husband informed me of what you did for us. You have my gratitude for handling the situation so honorably.
Have you found my sextant? nnOne of the crew probably took it. He's still guarding it jealously, even in death.nnThey were like that, you know.
Hello, my friend.  What is that you've got there?
You have passed this trial. nnSeek out the Trial of the Body if you haven't completed your tests. nnThe portal ahead awaits.
May the Eight bless you, friend!
Only one trial may persist at a time. nnYou are free to help your brethren.
Have you ever felt the pain of being separated from your true love? nnWhy can she not see how much I love her?
Nierre was weak. nnNot like the fine specimen I see before me....
Janne has left, and Murk-Watcher is one with the river. Knarstygg and Dro-Dara now return to a life of adventure.nnPerhaps you will see us again.
I saw what you did for Murk-Watcher. I cannot say that I understand, but I respect her right to choose her own fate.nnIt is time now for Dro-Dara and I to leave.
You must gather information about the invasion. Help the spirits of Crestshade find peace.
<<1>> no longer sings. Have you taken his heart?nnHurry. We must move quickly if we are to renew the song.
That was exciting, yes?
You're not from around here.
Move along, peasant. I can smell the beetle dung on your shoes.
I'm down ten silver. He must be cheating!
You ever walk by the slouchbear pens? You think they look pretty?nnMe neither. Was just asking. Ha.
What a fight! Jazha's a tough scrapper, isn't he?
This Blackmaul mercenary is dead.
Find my stolen pack. One of the ogres in Shinji's Scarp took it. It can't have gone far!nnPlease hurry. I'm not sure how much longer I can hold out.
Azura blessed us by bringing you to Gavaudon in our province's hour of need.nnThanks to you, our lands will soon return to normal, and my beloved Elin is finally home with me.
I'm looking for an ogre with a stolen pack. One of the other scouts is wounded, and the bandages are in that pack.
If it all falls apart in there  well, there's not going to be enough of us out here to stop the mass destruction that follows.nnGood luck.
How many of our own have we had to strike down? How many times have we watched them rise up again?nnThey do not know death. They will never find peace in the afterlife.
Quickly now! If you take too long burning the <<1>>s, the guards will surely notice me before I can escape!
Thanks again for helping me get out of that hole. I owe you one, mate.
Be mindful - there may be Imperial spies still lurking about town.

When you are fighting a monster wait for it to 'wind up' an attack. You may see the shimmering of magic or the lean back for a mighty punch. When you see the telegraph, hit your interrupt to stop the monster from attacking.
I feel restless, as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what it is.
I hear General Cruor pleaded with you, before you stepped on his throat!
You coming along was such a blessing.  nnTruly the Eight sent you! This will mean so much to Breloth. So much.
Down with the Empire!
By the Divines! You actually killed him! The scourge of the reach! The legend of the sea!nnI'm not sure what to do with myself now. Maybe I'll take up fishing again.
Have you found Ithguleoir? nnHe's in a cave in the waters north of the village. nnBe careful!
Have you found Ithguleoir? nnHe's in a cave in the waters north of the village. Be careful!
Have you found Ithguleoir? nnHe's in a cave in the waters north of the village. nnBe careful!
Ithguleoir is dead? I can hardly believe it! nnHenri can finally start fishing again. He certainly can't use Ithguleoir as an excuse anymore!
Cartesan Longleaf is convinced the noises in the woods are nothing more than natural wildlife.nnI am not so sure.
Those damn mercenaries killed our citizens. nnWe'll hunt them down, every last one of them!nnThey'll pay for what they did to Wind Keep.
Those damn mercenaries killed our citizens. We'll hunt them down, every last one of them!nnThey'll pay for what they did to Wind Keep.
I can't believe we were betrayed by our own kind. nnLuckily, I'm not above a little revenge.
More teeth. More teeth. I can't get enough. nnMy grandchildren will brag about their ancestors, and show off my trophy necklace.
<<1>> would like to thank you for saving <<2>>  and all of Gavaudon.nnMay the two moons smile kindly upon you.
It's pleasant to have company again. nnI must thank you for rescuing Glaynison.
We sent several soldiers up to that cave. Let me see, who were they? <<1>> was one. <<2>>, too.nnThey're good soldiers, unlike most of these fools.
This one must guard the chickens!nnRazha must make sure nothing happens to them!
Bring us the heart of a Blood Thorn Adept.
Are you leaving so soon, <<1>>? nnI don't want to trouble you, but if you see any wildflowers, it would be wonderful to hold them again.

Search the conscripts' corpses on the battlefield and bring me those chains.nnThat may seem harsh, but I have my family to consider. If I don't account for all the chains, they'll dock my pay. I've got brothers and sisters and kids to feed.
Marcel trusts Balcone. I don't.nnBe careful, <<1>>.

There was a pulse behind that door. Now it's drumming, drumming, drumming in my head and in my veins.nnI think I may need more blood soon. I feel light-headed. Did Balcone seem nervous? Maybe it's me.

Did Marcel send you? I suspected he might. I fear his ailment has addled his brain. I've seen that a lot lately.nnYou seem to be free of this fever. I wonder if you'd help me with a slight  complication.
You're welcome here anytime, <<1>>. I don't suppose a ghost makes the best drinking partner but a shade of a friend is better than none...
If you're looking for something wet that bites, just walk north. When you get in over your head and something drags you under, you'll know you've found it.
Have you found my sister yet? I can hear her cries from the cave.
Thank you so much for getting those rubbings for me. nnThey'll be the highlight of my rather extensive collection.
Please, you must burn the supplies. I will make my escape soon enough.
You're back, and with barely a scratch!
Find my husband and tell him that I died thinking of him.
Yes, this one can help you identify what you found.nnThat is the purpose of archaeology, is it not?
Be wary when you enter the temple, <<1>>. I hesitate to say that I do not trust Verin, but he has been acting strange of late.
The dizzying jolt of shock. The yowling trumpet of joy!
Lug is wanting to dance with the <<1>>.
Last we saw Lieutenant Gagnon, he was in the thick of the massacre in Moira's Hope. He must still be there now.
Thank you again. I can feel my wife's presence. nnAfter all I've done, I know she still loves me.
You did it. I couldn't believe it when I heard the crash, but you brought the whole place down.nnAlmost cost you your life.
You saved many here in Camlorn. I will mourn my wife privately, now.
Find my husband and tell him that I died thinking of him.

We should be attacking the ogres! <<1>> isn't going to free herself! Set the ogre totems on fire to provoke them into attacking. n nTry not to anger all of them. Pick them off a few at a time. We learned that after the first few attacks.
I still have work to do, but I'm told you found out who was behind those murders.nnIn fact, I heard you stopped them. Thank you, friend!
I still have work to do, but I'm told you found out who was behind all those murders, and you stopped them.nnThank you, friend.
Use the strange mechanism in front of the Infernal Device. nnI must leave for Razorvine Refuge and warn the advancing Aldmeri regiment of hte device's nature.
Daedric priests! Walking dead! Crocodile-faced monsters!nnMaybe I should just climb a tree and hide.
Shaking with anticipation. nnWaiting for stories! nnAnticipating the stories he will hear!
Are you ready to go get the Codex? The shadows are only getting longer, my friend.
I can't thank you enough. So many people in town just want to write her off. nnThey're less worried about her welfare than they are about who should take authority of Wind Keep.
I feel restless, as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what.
I feel restless, as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what it is.
I feel restless, as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what.
Watch your footing.
Bring the seedlings back here when you've got them. I'll be able to make some mischief with them.
I feel restless. It's as though Wind Keep is on the verge of something, but I don't know what.
What news? Have you thoroughly grizzled our enemies?

What a relief! I wouldn't have been comfortable just abandoning my companions, but if you're going to help them, that frees me up.nnAnd let me tell you, it feels good. I'm just not the settling-down type. I know that now.
My wife.... nnTo think it was only a few months ago we were married.nnNot so long ago, we were starting our new lives together.
I hope Alleim knows of a good remedy!nnI'll settle for anything that relieves his terrible fever.
Thank you for your assistance. nnWith so many of our resources focused on the war, we can certainly use the help.
I can't afford to be missing anyone in times like these.
I finally remembered the song! nnIt's called "The Orc's Bear," but I'm afraid it's not fit for mixed company.
I can concentrate on my studies again, but now I'm wondering if I want to continue with them.
Take that map to Queen Ayarynne in Elden Root to the north. You will find her in the Thalmor.
Those mushrooms will be the key to releasing me from this pain and suffering.
Please leave me alone. I have nothing to say to you.
That letter you found is no small matter. The Thalmor must be alerted at once.

This bile is a delicacy to Argonians, or so I hear. nnI doubt any half-civilized being could stand to be near it for very long. The smell is so foul!nnThe feeders are scattered about the farm. You should have no problem finding them.
I must gather my strength before I see her. nnI don't know if my spirit would persevere if I saw her in pain.....
