To see that symbol of my folly hurts me. I carry agony deep within my heart.nnI want my last moments to be free, unbound from the shackles of the temple's lies.
You've done a lot for us. We won't forget it.

No doubt the Ashlander mongrels want to sell or sacrifice the Tribunal's effigies. nnThey'll offer them up to whatever Daedric Prince they're worshipping! nnSlay the defilers. Take back our sacred symbols!
I never dreamed you'd find the Temple Master alive in there! nnTruly, you are a hero of the Tribunal!
The Vereansu Gulakhan holds the key to my bonds. I know not where they are within these walls, but I have no doubt that they will be well protected.
The Vereansu Gulakhan holds the key to my bonds. nnI know not where they are within these walls.nnI have no doubt that someone is defending them.
Behind the temple is a great waterfall. Meet me beneath its wake, and I will show you the way into the temple.
<You've found a sleeping body. At your touch, the Dunmer awakens with a start.>

It'll only be a matter of time before I'm forced to take action against the Ashlanders outside our walls.nnWe'll have to deal with both the Vereansu and the Matuul. I fervently hope I can resolve this conflict without shedding the blood of innocents.
My brother is down in the mines, guarding his secrets.nnI have a terrible feeling about this. Something's gone very, very wrong. Be careful!
When you are prepared, the yurt is now open to you.
Please deliver these to my husband and daughter. nnThey'll need them more than I will.
Nulenu is so selfless. I'll be reluctant to sell her things, so I hope the coin she provided will be enough.
What happened to the guards? You're reckless to attack them so brazenly!
You... you killed them!
How dreadful. I wish this could have been resolved without bloodshed.
I hope you're not here to report a missing friend or family member. nnThere's not much we can do until House Hlaalu sends more help our way.
I hear Seryan is planning to return to Mournhold. nnThe blessings of the Three never cease! I was about to strangle him.
Let the unarmed guards know. Their armaments are ready.nnAlthough my superiors are clearly incompetent, I will make sure Narsis does not fall.
My lady awaits you in the council chambers. They're in the northern section of Narsis. nnYou'll find them within the grand building overlooking the city.
So, do you have a good reason for interrupting my work?nnI can't think of what it would be.
My heartbreak will heal in time. The news of my death in this Dunmer war would destroy her, were this not done now.
Tell me, why did he give you this ring?
Hlerva! That rat! I should have throttled him when I had the chance.nnFind him. Make him pay.
My friend, I think I'm already on the mend. Thank you for showing me mercy!nnI'll just be on my way now....
Sergeant Olfin's impressed. Says you've got guts and you're fast on your feet. nnAssuming you can fight, I think we found the hero to finish these ogres off.
This is an occasion to celebrate! May the Eight bless you on your travels, friend!
Please! Help me! I don't want to die like this.
Hurry! Get to the top of that overlook! nnYou'll have to stop the Farseer before Vereansu reinforcements arrive. nnThey'll attack the Serk!
Please... help us.
Have you found Ranae? Is she safe?
Nethryn is too foolish to know what happened. nnI know the one who did this to me. They'll pay dearly.
Nethryn will pout for a while, but soon, he'll realize that this is his... our... life. nnMy family did not pay a dowry for me to have a philandering husband!
<<1>>, you've saved my life... twice!nnI chose my guards for their loyalty, but even they were seduced by this "Seeker."
I haven't ruled out anyone as a suspect, so you'll need to search everywhere for possible infractions. Collect anything you find, and I'll be able to make a case for tightening shipping security!
Greetings, traveller.nnIf you were planning to visit the graveyard behind me, you might want to come back later.
See that my father's sword is given to the caretaker. That will ease his mind.nnMy father and I can now rest for eternity, thanks to you and <<1>>.
Playing a dirty trick on Wud.nnWatching when he finds the lightning ants!nnLaughing until falling down.
Wud is comparing Hoom's dancing to that of a three-legged Slouchbear. The pain of its observation!
Nethryn is too foolish to know happened. nnI know who did this to me. They'll pay for this.
Pray at the cairns, and we will wipe these invaders from the keep.nnFor Princess Mira!
Nethryn will pout for a time, but soon, he'll realize that this isn't just his life. It's our life!nnMy family didn't pay a dowry for me to have a philandering husband!
I hear the ogres made their big push and you stopped them cold, took down a whole mess of them.nnGore and glory! Good work!
My father cannot rest, his shade forever wanders the catacombs. nnWould you help him find peace?

I... I can't believe my eyes. nnThe magical charge headed straight at the Obelus... and as if they were alive, the towers redirected the blast back at us!nnMy eyes must be deceiving me. What sorcery is this?
The pain... the agony... the unfilledl life I'll have to live....nnLet me die. Nothing will cure me! Nothing!
I thought everyone else was dead, but it brings great comfort to know I was wrong.nnI was wrong about our scouts, and more importantly, wrong about you.

I'm not sure who carried the potions. You'll want to check all the bodies. Be careful though, would you? nnThose Ogrim might not be the brightest of the bunch, but if you cross them, they'll rip you in two.

Do you know why I'm the most profitable merchant of my house, <<1>>? nnRisks! I'm willing to take risks! The others sit and whine like children when danger draws near.nnNot me! I'm like to get my hands dirty! Dirty... with filthy lucre.
Did you find my pack yet? nnI hope those things didn't tear it apart.

If you want to help, meet me at the Sia Ebony Mine. It's at the western end of the canyon.nnYou don't have to trust me. I mean, really! Who am I? nnAside from being the only one in this camp with more wits than a netch, I'm just another wanderer.
My sword is again broken, but this time for good, and for good purpose. She has forgiven me.nnYou have healed a wound that was centuries old.
Quite the find you've brought me! nnIf anything similiar finds its way into your hands, please keep me in mind.

I wonder what happened to the others. Did any of them make it?nnWe barely made a dent in there. We're back at square one with no clues about what happening in that canyon. nnSuch a senseless waste of life.

I can't... stop... yawning.nnMy mind is clearing with each breath. You've done it, haven't you? You've released me from this nightmare.nnWe'll awake to a new vision of peace for the Daggerfall Covenant.
We'll continue to Wayrest soon, now that our clan leader's business is done in this area.
Many strange things have happened recently. I'm sure that our clan leader will send word to us soon about our next assignment.
This area has many mineral deposits. I might stay here and start a business.

I'll dismiss the Blackmauls. I'll report my actions to the king. One way or the other, reparations will be made to my victims  even if I have to die to do it.nnYou haven't just saved my mind. You've given me a chance to redeem my honor.
Have you found my journal yet? My farmhouse is south of Shinji's Field beyond a field of pumpkins. nnYou have to keep that journal out of those mercenaries' hands!
I can't believe any of this happened.
It's good to finally be rid of those restraints.

The Orcs need to understand fear, so this never happens again.nnIf they think they can attack merchants and civilians in Elden Root and get away with it, they're sorely mistaken.nnRegardless of what the Imperials do, Orcs cannot just attack us.
I can't thank you enough. nnMy business is back on its feet, thanks to you.nnSpeaking of which, do you need anything? You're now my favorite customer!
Success! Hopefully, the Vereansu will be feeling the effects of this defeat for awhile.

I'm not sure who carried the potions. You'll want to check all the bodies. Be careful though, would you? nnThose Ogrim might not be the brightest of the bunch, but if you cross them, they'll rip you in two.
With that spirit silenced, I can finally get some rest at the wayshrine. nnThank you, <<1>>.
Verin has been destroyed, but not soon enough to save so many.nnLet me mourn Marcel a bit longer, please.

I'm not sure who carried the potions. You'll want to check all the bodies. Be careful though, would you? nnThose Ogrim might not be the brightest of the bunch, but if you cross them, they'll rip you in two.

Foul scion of the Direnni! How could you pass the trials of the faithful? No bastard elf-spawn would be so strong.nnDo you think to come here and put an end to the Maruhkites? We have survived much worse than you.
Did you see the two Imga to the north of here? I think one of them was going to go in and stop these mushroom-killers too!
Glad to see you back with us.
The one who holds my form enchanted must not have known I am a dreamwalker. I cannot stay outside of my body for long, however.
Only one trial may persist at a time.nnYou are free to help your brethren.
Only one trial can persist at a time.nnYou are free to help your brethren.
I believe that with your help, my sister and father can finally resolve their conflict.nnPerhaps then, they can finally be at peace.
The things I would do for this girl... they'll all be worth it in the end. I know it! nnI'll just need to keep thinking about her. Something will come to me.
The russula caps are deadly, but they're a key component of the spell I'm going to cast on you. nnThey grow in shady, moist places around our camp.

Greetings, Dream of <<1>>.nnDo not look so surprised. I can see your form, both awake and asleep, wandering the bridge between worlds. nnYou are a brave one to journey as Farseer Yamsi does. I pray for your success.
<You have found a dead body.>
You stand as the final hope of Rivenspire. I trust you will not disappoint us.
What now? How can I be expected to work with these constant interruptions?
I can't afford to be missing anyone in times like these.
Who let you in here? I'm in the middle of an important discussion.
If it wasn't for you and Brother Perry, I wouldn't have had the foggiest idea of what to do. Thank Azura for you both.nnBrother Perry's going to escort me back to Pariah Abbey. He's so brave.
It's finally over all of it.
Thank you for finding me. You were right, and I am forever in your debt.
So you found the fool whose bright ideas nearly got us killed?nnI'm surprised you didn't leave him to rot.
I had hoped my sisters would survive this poison , but I fear there is little else I can do now. I can only comfort them until the end.
After you're gone, I'll return to Adelphe and Tabakah.nnWhen you've got the last three artifacts, meet me at their camp to the south.nnMake sure you're not followed.
Your efforts have vexed the Supernal Dreamers to no end! nnThe Mages Guild appreciates your service.
You got the eggs back to them, didn't you?

The creatures of the forest all took part in Adyssa's loss.nnEvery one of them is responsible for what happened here.nnWhen Adyssa got back to the camp, all that was left was the shoe of this one's friend. What he must have endured....

I've not thought much about it, but the shells of dreugh could be crafted into decent sets of armor. If we can't get the Ebony mines back as ours again, we can at least get some soldiers here and clear the mines ourselves while making a nice profit.
Friend, hold a moment. I have a favor I would ask of you.

That robe fits you well. You look perfect! Like a perfect idiot.nnNo, wait! That came out wrong. I meant to say those cultists are idiots. You look just like them. Because you're disguised. In a robe.nnUm... I think I should stand guard or something.
I can't go home yet. Not until I catch my breath.nnYou have to find out who's responsible for this. Whoever it is must pay for what he did to us!
Sarvyl has been acting different lately. nnHe even looks different... and it's colder here now.nnIt's so cold here.
You've got a funny glow around you, stranger. It's kind of unnatural. nnHave you been visiting the ruins up north?
Have you spoken to <<1>> yet?nnI grow impatient, acolyte.

I can feel it! I can feel the Master's Power! nnI feel it in every part of my body. Every part! And I must....nnWait. Why are you still here? Did I not give you a task?nnDo not disturb my cosmic meditations. Begone!
I dispatched Tomal more quickly than I expected. nnI have his crystal shard.nnHow did you fare with Dalomer?
Talk to my wife please. I'm still weak from my ordeal.
Have you found my stolen wine? If I don't make this delivery, I'm ruined!
That took you long enough. I've been in there so long, I was finding it hard to move.
You must hurry. I don't know how long the dreugh will keep them alive. nnThey're in the slum quarter north of here.
Have you found Relah?

Now that Claude and Pierre got their just desserts, Andre and I can rejoin the gang! Thanks, stranger! nnBy the way: we never met, and this never happened. I call it "plausible deniability."nnGood day to you, stranger!
Did you get the ring  Miranda?
You should have killed that Baron Sorick.nnThough I suppose that would have just caused more trouble. Maybe what you did was for the best. He's leaving, and my husband's alive.
It's as though I've been under a spell until you arrived! nnI really should go home soon.
They work in the paddies. They work in the household. nnThat despicable man doesn't care how he uses his slaves. He's a scoundrel!nnThey must be freed, and he must pay with his life!
Another one of those troublemakers, eh? I won't stoop to your level. Your kind disgusts me.nnBut wait... you aren't with them, are you? My apologies, friend! Please forgive me. What can I do for you?
Speak to Uvela. Hear the lies behind his words. nnHe's working to destroy this plantation, and I have no doubt House Dres is behind it all.

There must be some kind of contaminant in the water. That's the only reasonable answer!nnI'd wager this has something to do with the new help Govyn's hired. nnThose thugs couldn't harvest a paddy if their mothers were starving for salt rice.
You're back. Does Master Vinden have his shipment?
Don't tell Shaleen I sent you. nnIf he knows I'm here, he'll try to leave.
When the Mabrigash bring their victims here, they leave supplies for them.nnSince most of the husks simply give up on living, I take what they don't!nnWaste not, want not, as I say!
I believe I said "good day."nnMy clients will be most displeased.

I've spent enough time in this hovel of a village.nnI must wait until my retinue arrives before I can return to Mournhold. nnI do hope my servants have drawn a bath for my return. This village is filthy.
My memory of what happened has long left me. nnI cling to the memory of the one who doomed me to this.nnI remember Ervyna.
<<1>>! You've found the evidence I need! nnQuickly! We must gather more. These creatures must not leave the mines!

My mistress is particular about her wine. I know that the ingredients I've gathered will change the taste of the cheap wine to something more appealing.nnStill, I'm clumsy. I'll break more bottles if I try to mix the ingredients myself.
Today, your actions have saved Aldsotha.
The soldiers are doing all they can to keep the temple protected. nnI just hope we can hold out until this battle's over.
I'm so worried about Endal. I haven't seen him since the attack. nnI can only hope he made it Mournhold before all of this happened.
<<1>> seems trustworthy enough. nnI'd believe her word any day.
Please do not disturb this cargo. It is quite fragile and contains many delicate magical tools.
I was in such a hurry, I left my stall wide open. nnBildrin is a fool. That ruthless skinflint should have fled when he had the chance.
Welcome back, <<1>>. nnI hope your audience with the Tribunal went well. nnIt's an honor to meet someone who was come face-to-face with the Three.

I cannot tell you how torturous my existence has become! I cannot help the elder, for I know this task is not for me. nnI have seen my failure in the stars. You must do this. You must find her. nnWe can do nothing without her guidance.
I, Zairrm-dar, am more than happy to go out of his way to help those who help him. You have helped Zairrm-dar, and can sample some of Zairrm-dar's wares.
How weak I feel! nnI fear if you had taken longer to arrive, I would be no more.
You have come, sparking hope, but what happens if the flame should catch?
My companions don't deserve to be punished for my foolishness.nnFind them. Release them. I can only hope they'll forgive me.
That's a nice looking ring you have there.  I would be interested in trading one of my hand crafted weapons for it.  Look them over and lets discuss it.
I do not deserve forgiveness. I do not deserve Brelayne's love. nnI was stupid and careless with her heart. nnI don't expect to be worthy of her love again.
I would love to have that necklace.  My wife loves fine jewelry.  I would be willing to trade you one of my handcrafted armors for it.
We dare not let Aldsotha fall under the control of Daedra. nnAny assistance you could offer would be most salutary.
I've heard you're helping both <<1>> and <<2>>.
I was hoping to see the lighthouse bonfire ablaze by now.
I bet it felt good to take down <<1>>. I would've been mad as Malacath that I couldn't kill him at that parley you had.
In truth, I missed Nelin terribly. nnI couldn't face him when I heard what he'd done to me... to us.
There's so much work to be done to get this place back in working order.
This <<1>> will get you inside the ruins. From there you must locate the <<2>> on your own.
Your help has been invaluable. You've drawn the thorn from this plantation's side. nnIn time, we may prosper again.
You have been paid for your services, I have other things to attend to at the moment.
Go now. Use that scroll near the large fire.nnI'll get Durak and myself to the abbey with the Scroll of Return.
Those mushrooms will be the key to releasing me from all of this pain and suffering.
That storm spirit! It's incredible!nnDid you summon it with the scroll? I've never seen anything like it!
Have you found the information you needed?
You woke Durak. Incredible. nnI have no doubt Azura herself sent you. You will find the Dream Shard, my friend. You will save us.
Don't think I'm going to let that useless oaf off the hook so easily. nnHe'll suffer for trying to leave me. Trust me. I know how to make someone suffer.
The madness has lifted. By the Eight, what was I thinking? nnThe last thing I need now is a child draining my savings.
I'm never drinking a glass of wine again... or a bottle... or a bucket....nnMara, my head hurts. At least I'm free of the madness.
I almost killed my closest friend over a chunk of gold no bigger than a pea. What was I thinking?nnThank you for saving me from that madness.
Our fields are safe, but the Dream Shard is gone. I have no idea how I failed to see the theft, but I will not fail Durak again.
Thank you for saving our fields. It's too bad we couldn't stop the thief who stole the Dream Shard.
I'm so embarassed. My actions during the Fervor were... I can't even describe them.nnPlease never speak to me about this again.
I thank the Divines for the spirit wardens. nnI don't know if I can ever repay them. They took good care of me during the Fervor.nnThey kept me from doing things I'd really regret today!
Please, go to Sister Safia.nnAnd may the Divines bless you.
You put out the fire! Maybe this situation is about to start turning around.

The form to which I shall return is in your hands.nnThe creatures here claim many victims. What you will gather from them is unknown to me. nnI simply wish to live again. It's been far too long since I've felt the ground beneath my feet.
RETURN MY MOTHER'S NECKLACE!
Your time is limited. If the Mabrigash strip the soul from this courier, he will be nothing but an empty shell.nnHardly useful for questioning, I would think. Make haste.
Ah, it's you.
Still alive, then? Best if you leave, before that changes.
So... you're back.
Melesi sent you to retrieve our scroll? Ah, well! You'd best be going then, right?
You're awake! Oh, thank you for saving our Abbot.
I failed Stormhaven. I failed everyone.
Ah yes. The <<1>> who spoke for the Bosmer outside Razorvine.nnI ordered you killed, as I recall.
My wife and I both thank you.
Did you get the wards in place?
Hail the Champion of the Bloodfields!
You're a legendary gladiator!
I am in the presence of greatness.  You are the Champion of the Bloodfields.
You are a worthy Champion.  Maybe one day you will fight with our royal guard.
Hurry up! Untie me and help me escape!
Anything. Please. Just help me.
The dagger is cursed to draw from the souls of the living, using their blood as an anchor to harness the spell.nnTake care not to cut yourself.
It was an honor to challenge such a skilled <<1>>.
We're going home? Oh, I do miss my bed.
I'm glad someone finally sees sense in getting out of here.
They've finally gotten what they deserve.nnMay they rot in the depths of the unliving.
Use the Vault Vines in Altmertown to leap onto buildings and spread flowers there with the Flowering Spindle.nnKeep an eye out for the Altmer Wardens, though. They're grumpy and don't like flowers.
We've managed to survive... somehow.
Aphren's Hold is west of here, along the road that connects Wayrest to Bangkorai.nnI will meet you there.
So you think you can defeat our champion, <<1>>? nnI've yet to decide if you're brave or foolish.

Well now, <<1>> appears at last. Good to see you again - especially back among the living.nnThe old man is waiting for you upstairs. He hasn't stopped talking about you since we got here. Come on, I'll walk you up.
Make your questions brief. nnThis man wearies me with his incessant yelling.
You are no mere mortal. I can sense your spirit, even within this dream. It is powerful.nnPerhaps we will meet again.
I have seen your journey in my dreams, long before I was trapped here.nnLittle did I realize we would meet in those same reveries.
You'll find beetles all through the caves here. If you start running low, check right outside the tunnel. They tend to gather in the open.
Goblins have killed my comrades. nnIt's time for revenge.
Have you found my children?
Please you must help me!  I'm being held here against my will.  I will forever be in your debt.  Will you help me?
I only share information with those who are smart enough to know what to do with the information.  You don't look intelligent.  Prove me wrong?
Did they send you to finish me off?

<<1>>, you return as Champion of the Bloodfields.  I am a man of my word.  I will arrange for Vestriel's freedom.  Valoria and Vestriel will meet you at a rock covered area in the woods to our South. Make sure no one follows you.
Have you gathered nature's primal power?
I have nothing left to offer the spirit wardens. Nothing. Not even time.nnMay your sleep be blessed by visions and dreams, my friend.
Have you gathered magic's mystic power?
They're draining people, taking their life from them in a horrible, twisted way.nnSadir needs to pay for what he's done to my men... and for what he intends to do to me!nnHe must be stopped.
You've saved my love from the Supernal Dreamers! Thank the stars!
I'd prefer if you just killed me now instead of turning me over to my comrades.
Hurry! Find the key! nnOne of those dead soldiers might have it. Did you check them?
Make it quick. Can't you see I'm bleeding to death here?
We've managed to survive... somehow.
Untie me, and I can help you free Farmer Vanne from his eternal sleep.
You can find the portals to close all around the countryside here. Be careful - it's not an easy task.
What remains of my old life is scattered to the marshes. It is as it should be.nnThere is only one more step. You must return to my brother, Ah-Nakul. Give him my tail.
Plucking those damned weeds? Good work!
Who are you? You're not my normal courier.
Rrrrrr....
Hssssss!
Please do not disturb me. I am in the middle of my devotions.
You will always be welcome and safe in our swamp, <<1>>.
I know my husband is trapped inside his own body. nnThere's only one way he can free himself from the madness possessing him.nnHis only hope of freedom is through death.
You will find the cauldron in the center of the swamp, west of my home.

You've taught me a valuable lesson. nnI must admit, I can't let go of my anger against <<1>>, but it's worse knowing others are suffering because of what I've done.nnMy husband and son would never forgive me. I have to find a way to atone for that.
I hope you'll return with good news from <<1>>. nnI can't imagine life has been easy for her lately.
I've told you all that I'm going to tell you.
The pain never ends. It never ends.
At last, we have our guar back and... most of our belongings.

It's never a mistake to explore more than one path, <<1>>. You're welcome to return to runecrafting. I'm pleased to see you, in all honesty.nnOf course, you'll need to start fresh, as any other supplicant would. Excuse me. I meant to say "applicant."
Tell me what you found in that smuggling den. I must have evidence!

I should warn you. The effects of that elixir can be rather potent. Be cautious while it runs through you.nnOh, and mind yourself around the nix-hounds in the area. They might smell the elixir and be drawn to you.
You're taking Nardan's advice? It's your funeral, s'wit.
Hello, citizen.nnNo, I don't like calling people "citizen," but the Altmer start sputtering when I don't.
The captain is sound asleep.
I'm a little busy now, if you can't tell. nnOthrina will have my hide if we miss this shipment.

I'm awake nowthe nightmare is over. My mind is clear. nnMemories are confused, but I know I did terrible things. The Midnight Union went horribly bad. So I've disbanded it. That was the right thing to do, wasn't it?
Get out of my sight, cur.
I think I may actually get some enjoyment out of this party afterall now.
Though I am relieved, something tells me as long as Lady Adima is around, the threat of death will always loom over me.

Again, you have my thanks. If only I could be there to see the look on Hosni's face when you hand it to him.nnAnd it seems you also gained the robes of a Supernal Dreamer? Those should come in handy should you ever need to leave the grounds.
I hope you could gather some helpful information from the others.
What do you have there?
Have you found any of their spies? I would like to ensure that they do not exploit our good will in dealing with them.
This one is beyond help.
I saw many of my fellow wardens make it to safety. Thank you.nnIt's so ironic that we rely on a stranger's help after being attacked by those we considered friends.
I think I have to p- I have to step behind a tree.nnOh. Not anymore, I guess.
You must destroy the alarms positioned around Leaftower before any more Eladrim troops are slain trying to infiltrate.
Do you remember who I am? nnGods, I wonder what those Mabrigash have done to your mind.
We'll protect the Mabrigash with our lives.nnEverything we are, we owe to them.
It's so strange... I feel at peace suddenly. Like a weight lifted off of my shoulders.nnI'm unsure of what brought it on.

Ugh! Suddenly, my mind is so hazy.nnI feel as though my memories have been lost to me, yet I remember everything, as if it had just happened. nnI'll need to clear my thoughts if we're going to help the Mabrigash.

I don't know how, but I fear the Mabrigash have gotten into the camp. My guard wore those amulets for protection, but they've been bewitched!nnI must contemplate this. You must go. If you delay, I hold no guarantee of what awaits you.
Please, stranger, I beg you to do this for us. nnGharvin is my life. If I were to lose him, I'd have no reason to live.
The very idea of Stental accusing me makes my blood boil. I'd like to see the evidence!
Did I hear you right? Did you say Geon is under investigation for the murder of Rahar?

Your help with both these matters is much appreciated. Until that damn guillotine's been dismantled, I won't be able to sleep. nnAnd more importantly, until the matter in Rivenspire is resolved, the Covenant will be severely weakened.

You are the one Valeor told me to expect?nnYes... I can sense the Mabrigash magic deep within you. I had not felt its presence before. The magic must slowly be fading.nnYou will need an Amulet at once.
My mind is clearer now, but there are still things I cannot remember. Perhaps it is better this way.
What's this? Can't you let a man enjoy a moment's rest? Are you telling me King Emeric needs this bench right now?
Those bastards were lying to us! I should have listened to Ilerian.
I've paid my debt in full. Off with you now!
Like I said, if you need to talk to the captain, you'll have to catch him up at the Cloudy Dregs.
My mind is clearer now, but there are still things I cannot remember. Perhaps it is better this way.
If you want to tangle with those bandits, that's your own business, but don't drag me into it.
Christophe's will was strong. That was the only way he could have resisted their torture for so long.nnI'm certain he died without regrets.nnPlease, you must go. I'll return to Pariah Abbey shortly.
Hilani is sorry her warning to the Spirit Wardens came late, but this one is grateful you went to their aid.
Now, go.nnMy sisters have already begun to work their magic, blinding the Guard. They will not remember what happened. You are free to leave. I would advise that you not return, <<1>>.
Now, go.nnMy sisters have already begun to work their magic, blinding the Guard. They will not remember what happened. You are free to leave. I would advise that you not return, <<1>>.
Any sign of Anabi? She should be somewhere in the ligorcap fields.
You again! I hope those other Ashlanders haven't managed to lure your money into their purses. nnIt's sad how few people can resist the urge to drink, gamble, and waste their lives with skooma.
Are you going to eat that? Can I?

I fear the Mabrigash haven't brought my guards to any of the surrounding areas. Call it a hunch. nnI'll find them, though.nnI'd leave if I were you. More of the witches will arrive soon. You don't want to be here for that.
We're in your debt for your timely assistance.
I'll be all right. I'm hurt, but I'll live. nnBut I think I've been here long enough. I'm heading for points east.
I don't want your charity.
I hope you find the man who murdered my husband. I want to see him hang!
What do you want?
If I were you, I'd take the bottle and get drunk somewhere far from the water!
Find the wretch who murdered Burob, and I will happily strangle him for you.
No one believes me. No one's going to avenge her.
You'll need to find that man and question him.nnBe quick about it. If he's a spy, you'll need to ensure he never makes it back to Mournhold.
This can't be happening. It can't be. nnI bet everything I had on Jazha!
It can't be true. It can't be. I bet everything I had on Jazha!
The best part of the fights is when they're done. Everyone who bet on the winner gets to split the loser. Some of those tigers are really tasty.
It's not that I like seeing blood. It's that I like winning money.
It can't be true. It can't be. I bet everything I had on Shanari!
It can't be true. It can't be. I bet everything I had on Shanari!
I'm so worried about Endal. I haven't seen him since the attack. nnI can only hope he made it to Mournhold before all of this happened.
Several spirit wardens gave chase into this cavern. nnYou must free any spirit wardens they've captured... before it's too late.
You must save Christophe. Please hurry!
Thanks to your efforts, Colette and Rhian were able to get past the cultists and reach the cave entrance. Join them there. I'll catch up!
You can save us and all of Menevia, but only if you can stop them before it's too late!
Have you found the key? One of those Supernal Dreamers has it.
Glad the Abbey sent help. We need it.
Whoever these cultists are, they've taken over the Moonlit Maw.
Please, help Ograk as he has asked.
Part of me doesn't want to open the letter, as if the action itself would make the fear of his death a reality.
I'm very busy, if you can't tell. What's your business here?
Do what you must. I won't be moved.
Do what you can. This man could end all of Deshaan!
I hope Mender Sarvyl didn't cause irreversable damage to the people of Deshaan.
Did you get those orders to Razorvine? I think my sister and I will stay at Woodberth for a while and help the soldiers get through the forest.
I saw you fight <<1>>. You were amazing!
I watched you fight in the ring. I was rooting for you the whole time! It's an honor to meet you.
All sold out? Well done!
Of course, if this had been a real fight, I would have disemboweled you immediately.nnThat sort of thing happens in a real fight!
Hey, thanks for the help! I'm almost out of here, don't worry about me.
Please slay the abomination I summoned. It lingers still, under the water.
I'm glad you're safe.nnDid you get the Dream Shard?
Thanks to you and Uradasou, I should be able to find my family again.
Those Ashlanders got exactly what they deserved.
Thanks to you, we took out all the Vereansu... even though we were outnumbered!
From now on, I'm protecting this signal fire with my life. nnAnyone who wants to put it out will have to go through me.
Just untie me. I'll make it to Koeglin Village on my own.
Without Helene, life isn't worth living!nnI'll just sit here and die.
Hey! Are you <<1>>? Someone gave me this message. nnIt's got your name on it.nnHa! What a fool.
Unless you have information on the fugitive, I must insist you be on your way.
Don't trust any of those foreigners. They're here to take advantage of the new peace under the Daggerfall Covenant.
Pulled it off again, and pulled one over on Ma'jhad Kha to boot!nnYou are a character straight out of a storybook. I hope we cross paths again.
Quickly! Get to the top of that overlook! nnYou'll have to stop the Farseer before the Vereansu reinforcements arrive.nnThey'll attack the Serk!
Hopefully, the supplies you brought will keep the nobles happy for a while.
If I recall, Barnabe is also on duty with Geon right now. I'm sure that has something to do with his anger.
You may have defeated our champion, but we're still watching you.
Not often do I see the selflessness you displayed when returning those deeds. I admit, I did not wish to welcome you as some of the others did, but now I see their wisdom.
You defeated our champion? nnI don't care. I don't have time for your kind.
I've lived in Wayrest all my life, and I still get turned around inside the city walls.
Please do not disturb me.nnI'm in the middle of my devotionals.
The Prophet's portal stone will get you to the ruins. From there, you must locate the Balac on your own.nnGo with caution, <<1>>. Gods only know what else you'll find in there.
Be sure to tell your friends where they can get more of these exotic delights!
I hope those rumors turn out to be nothing but paranoia. So, did you get those hides?
I must return to Pariah Abbey and rejoin my brothers. Our sacred duty is protecting Menevia. nnMay the Divines protect you.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?
Thanks, <<1>>! Those ropes were really tight.
My memory of what happened has long left me. nnI cling to the memory of the one who doomed me to this.nnI remember Ervyna.
Have you sought the treasure I spoke of? nnQuickly! Waste no time in seeking it.nnIts rewards will defy your wildest dreams.

Your deeds of valor helped us protect this school. nnWe're one step closer to destroying the evil that dwells here.nnIt's time for us to delve deeper. We must destroy the evil's source... once and for all!
Why do you tarry here? Why do you remain? nnI would think you'd have learned your lesson by now.nnI thought you would be long gone from this place.
Go. Go!nnI'll be fine. You have to help Elvira!
You dealt with the brigands? Great! nnLet Duke Nathaniel know. I'd go myself, but I can't leave this merchant unprotected.
My memory of what exactly happened has long left me. I cling to the memory of the one who doomed me to this: Ervyna.
The key to my cage is in Ma'jhad's quarters.

Things will get back to normal soon, hopefully in time for planting. nnI can't wait to get back to tilling the soil again and tending my crops.nnSoil needs tilling. Crops need planting. I'll be waiting.
There's no shame in losing to skill like yours.nnWell fought, stranger.
It feels good to be free again. Thank you!
That'll show those loud-mouthed braggarts! nnYou're one we can count on, you are.

The poison is inside a crate in one of the storage buildings down by the docks but they may move it at any time.nnOnce you've poisoned the wine don't forget to come back and tell me all about it. I can't wait to see them swell and die before me.
The device exploded as we were taking the town. Luckily, none of us were hurt.
I have no words that can express the kindness you've done for me and Danabi.nnYou are honored among us, stranger.
You! You can see me? Am I not a spirit trapped on this plane?
Listen closely! The orders of our masters must not be ignored! nnThey will rain death upon the unbelievers, the n'wah who taint our lands!
Vemar was a good man. I trained under him for many years in the temple. nnWhat could have caused him to go astray?
I was... dreaming? I don't remember anything.
What... where am I? nnI feel so weak....
You have the potion you need to beat Grul in a fight. nnSlaughter that Orc like he slaughtered my master!

We are of a like mind, <<1>>.nnAlthough we demonstrate sophisticated tastes, we still need action and blood to inspire us.nnMy Midnight Union will let me know when you've left Hammerdeath. Then I'll meet you at my estate.

As I descended into madness, I fled to my room and seized a glass orb.nnMy mother gave me the orb as protection against evil. The relic warded off my madness long enough for me to make my escape.nnLook for it when you go to save my friends!
That's it! nnThe orb's enchantment worked on me. There's no reason it shouldn't work on the others, right?
I think you have something for me.  Do you bear the love letters, my friend?
I don't have time for the likes of you.
<<1>> thinks she can get away with this treachery. nnAfter all, no one would suspect a lesser race of such powerful magic. nnI am not so easily fooled!
I must prepare the remedy. nnYou must find the memories of the mad ones.

Feel free to board the Midnight Swell. It's not going anywhere. I'll bet they're hiding something in their hold.nnTheir captain is as dishonest as the day is long. nnDon't ask me how I know. I just know it.
I've got my eye on you, stranger. Don't try anything foolish.
You must stop the food destined for my village. If you don't, countless people will suffer.nnSurely, I'll be cursed for my greed in the afterlife.
This village has survived many trials. We'll survive countless others to come. nnI mustn't be rash in my thoughts or my actions.nnThank you for your help.
Thanks for the help! I'll try to avoid being snared again.nnCan't be delayed by any more... budding problems! Ha!nn...ha? Oh, come on.
Enter the portal to the four shrines. nnWithin, you will face the trials of the Dunmer people, just as Vivec once did, blessings upon his name.nnThe way ahead is perilous, my friend.

You're not the first one to ask questions, nor shall you be the last. nnI don't expect you to understand my reasoning, since you're merely mortal.nnIn time, the truth will be clear to you. Like all, you must have patience and endure.
Unless someone can stop Patriarch Leyden, he'll corrupt all of House Dres to suit his twisted purposes. nnThis must not come to pass.
Kindness, even in this desolate place. nnNever would I have thought to find kindness here, much less from a stranger!nnPerhaps you're just a dream. I can't tell truth from falsehood anymore.
I saw the fireball from here. That was incredible!
Did you find the ones responsible for this madness?
If you kill the undead, it will free me. Please, I do not wish to remain here anymore.
Even the king crocodile falls before you. Amazing!nnA spectacular act of reptilian regicide!
There's already a beast in the arena. nnCome back when you've used that one up. Or vice versa.
Great work, <<1>>! nnIt looks like that scarecrow will keep the scamps away for a while.
Welcome to Koeglin Village Inn, my friend! What'll you have?
Have you found him yet? The poor thing! He's just a guarling!
It's a shame abut the Duchess, but I hear things have settled down at Castle Alcaire. That's a relief.
Unless you have information on the fugitive, I must insist you be on your way.
Oh, my head! What happened?

Search for a pristine scamp skin, a ritual candle, and a Dremora heart. Then look for Farmer Vanne at Stonebridge Mill.nnYou must use the right ingredients in the right order. Only then can you free Farmer Vanne from his enchanted sleep.
A fine job you've done, <<1>>! nnYou must have defeated the Daedra, for I see my daughter is safe.

I'm trying to find a way into the lower levels. I believe the answer to our problems with Kellisa is somewhere down there.nnMy divinations have shown me she's siphoning dark magic from an unknown source.
Huh? What's going on? I can't move!
We treated the roots, but the groundwater was fouled. nnThe cleansing is not complete.
The amulet has belonged to my family for generations. nnIt bears a distinct crest, though I never knew its origin.nnHowever, I... don't feel quite right when I'm wearing it.
<This hen has bright blue eyes.>
Those spies you killed belonged to House Dres. I recognized their armor from here. I would have joined the fight if this alit hadn't attacked me.
You have done what I thought no one could. nnSuch a selfless act!  I've never seen anything like it. nnWe all owe you a great debt.

The Exalted Master is our leader here in Deshaan. nnThough she isn't the Grandmaster of the Morag Tong, she holds power over many officials here.nnYou'll need my guild emblem to gain access, so you can see her.
Your actions have saved Shad Astula. nnSomeday, we'll rebuild again, thanks to you.
You're alive. Were you successful?
My family moved to Wayrest. As soon as I can, I'm going to join them.

Complete the writs my Thinkers present to you, and I promise the knowledge you seek shall be yours. nnYou'll find my three Thinkers in contemplation throughout the camp.nnDo hurry, <<1>>. It's not polite to keep a lady waiting.
Let's get out of here!
I'll stay here, just in case any of the others escaped. nnI have to hope some of the nobles of our house weren't swayed by the false ideals of that madman.

Lagrayn is a disgrace. His very presence insults the Morag Tong. nnHe murders for sport, yet his hand in deception is swift. He blinds the ordinators who would suspect otherwise.nnHe might not seem too bright, but he won't fall easily.

Aldsotha is east of here. nnLagrayn is drunk somewhere on the city streets. He's wailing his ballads. He's caterwauling horrible off-key tunes. nnI'm sure no one will mind if you bring silence to those streets.nnEveryone will sleep better at night.
Am-ri is an Argonian, so don't go looking for pointy ears out on the road.nnCheck west of Aldsotha for her group. nnThey tend to favor the marsh area, so you may have luck there.
I'm right behind you. Lead the way.
Hurry up. Untie me before it's too late!
Dooon't worry. I'm going, I'm going... jusht as shoon as this ground shtops moving. Shtay shtill!nnThere's a reashon I'm a wandering bard, y'know.
Hmm. Aren't you a peculiar specimen ? nnWait a minute. You're not a Goblin! I know Goblins inside and out, and you're no Goblin. You're the one from the Watch!
Look for Arcady or his wife, Adiel, in the slums to the east.
Have you collected S'Rashi's debts?
Have you spoken to <<1>> yet? nnBefore we can get to work, we really need to get those guar delivered.
Has anyone seen Hlena? nnAnyone?
By the Lord, Mother, and Wizard, our prayers have been answered!
Maybe I can squeeze in one last drink before I leave....
Maesar Odim is currently occupied with watching his work mangle their contenders. You should be able to get to his tent easily to examine the ledger.
While watching Teshmul, you'll have the run of the place. None of my mercenaries should get in your way.
Rescue the others. They're in the cave, probably trapped in cages like this one.

I'm sure you've had quite enough of these little games, but I'm afraid there's more to come.nnThis next one is easy. You'll choose who you slaughter, as you are wont to do, and send her back to Oblivion. The other one I will... unmake.
You can't get better odds than these!
Need a little drink to loosen up?
I bet I'm going to be having nightmares for a long time after all this.nnTimes like these I miss having my father around.
If you can't hold your drink, don't expect me to clean you up.nnYou can pay those hussies over there instead.
Care to hear a song? I have a lovely one... just for you.
I hope you don't intend to spend all your time loitering around here.
I thought for sure I had chosen a winner. nnMy luck will change next time.
Watching these alits is almost frightening. nnI've never seen them so ferocious in the wild!
See anything you like?
Move along, traveller.
My next assignment is in Daggerfall. At least it's bigger than Alcaire.
I know now the spiders aren't a Redguard plot.nnStill a damned nuisance, though.
You have the elixir? The vial is not cracked?
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
Our noble house is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
These are unfortunate events, yes, but mourn not for my wayward son. His impropriety has paid him in kind.nnMy daughter will see this mess repaired.
Our noble house is in your debt. nnLet me know if I can be of any further service.
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
I'm glad the madness is finally ended.
I'm sorry I acted like such a buffoon. I don't know what came over me.
It's like a bad dream has ended. Thank you for stopping the madness.
It's so nice to be able to think clearly again.
I'm sorry I accused you of being a spy.
I can't believe we were all at each other's throats. It's disgusting.
I think everyone was paranoid, but that doesn't excuse my behavior.
I'm sorry I threatened you. You saved us all.
You do yourself credit, <<1>>!nnYou've turned this nightmare into a peaceful dream again.
I knew there was something going on around here! I just knew it!nnThings can get back to normal now. The sooner, the better, if you ask me.
This House is in your debt. Let me know if I can be of any service.
The ruins are awake? How fascinating! Lord Saren has such amazing fortune.nnWhat a time to be stuck out here, waiting for the patriarchs to notice me.
Getting sick of staring at so much land. Give me the open sea any day.
Getting sick of staring at so much land. Give me the open sea any day.
Where did you wander off?

You got the <<1>> safely to the base camp? That's welcome news.nnI'll admit, we're no closer to figuring out how to turn this thing off again. nnFortunately, the automunculi don't want to come down here.
They say we owe you our lives, <<1>>, and perhaps I do. But I am strong as well and will continue to work hard.
I became a sailor so I could see the world.
Getting sick of staring at so much land. Give me the open sea any day.
I hope the Midnight Swell's crew doesn't hold things against us. They're good for business, after all.
I could've been a sailor if I'd wanted to, you know. I just decided that life in the village was better for me, that's all.
My brother is somewhere in the mines. I tried to follow him, but it's dangerous in there - something's gone very, very wrong. Be careful!
Did you find that villain? Did you make him pay?
Untie me from this post before someone sees you! I can't take another one of Jharad's note taking sessions.

They've been questioning us about Evermore since they captured the village. My wounds are a testament to that.nnI only hope the lighthouse was destroyed soon enough. There's no telling what information they've already passed along.
Find my sword. Kill the Omen. Please.
Mm? Yes?
I've asked Saren not to disturb me when I'm listening. Still he brings gawkers.nnWhat is it you want?
What do you want, stranger?
Have you visited other Dwemer ruins? Have you seen a Centurion before? I have so many questions about these devices.
You're still alive! How did it go in the cave?
I've got my eye on you, stranger. Don't try anything foolish.
What? Yes, I'm Govran Cerone.nnAre you here to kill me? To take me to a false trial before a crooked magistrate? nnWhat is it? What do you want? What do any of you want from me?
Did you get in there yet? Did you find him? nnThe poor thing! He's just a guarling!
I'm not afraid of these people. They're my neighbors. At least, they were.nnDid you find what you came in here for?
It's you! Are you all right?
Run along. Fetch your reward atop this tower.nnAnd mind your footing. I don't want to lose my most loyal subject.
I'll never leave Koeglin Village. I want to put the past behind me.nnI want to walk away from all that fear and madness.nnThis is my home.
Gag! I didn't realize the stench of burning bodies would be worse than the stench of rotting ones. Let's just hope the trolls won't like it either.

The Reachmen aren't going to kill themselves. Kill Reachmen in Dunkarn Haven to avenge the deaths of my fellow troopers.nnReport to Constable Didier at the camp southeast of the village when you're finished.
Please, go quickly. My strength has grown, and I must confess, the temptation to try to bind you to me grows as well. nnIf you remain, it could be dangerous  for both of us. Just go.
I'm quite grateful. nnThank you for getting the <<1>> safely back to us. We'll need her input.
Untie me, and I can help you free Farmer Vanne from his eternal sleep.
I came back here to find the patterns, but they're gone. nnThere's no point in staying here now. nnCould you get me out of here?
How did the Dwemer Tonal Architects concentrate in this cacophony? It's so noisy here!nnHow could they possibly make magicka vibrate in sympathy with their will?
Huh? What am I going to do with this centurion core? nnOh, I'm going to study it in my tent, of course. Intensely... for hours.nnI expect it will take me a long time to master its intricacies.
I say! You again!nnI thought it would be best to come back here. It's safer here! nnThat large centurion wandering around out there can't fit in the door... or so one would hope.
I've studied Dwemeris for so long! I still don't understand them. nnTheir thoughts are as alien to me as a Daedra's.
Maybe I'm not cut out for this life, after all. nnMaybe I should withdraw to the stacks of my Great House's archive.
<You have found a body. This young scholar was rent asunder by by the slashing blades of Dwemer automunculi.>
Being stationed at Eagle's Gate puts us at the crossroads of two of the gloomiest regions in all of Tamriel. nnJust my luck, I guess.
We've heard reports of strange things happening in Rivenspire.nnIf that's where you're headed, be careful.
There's no shame in losing to skill like yours. Well fought.
There's no shame in losing to skill like yours. Well fought, stranger.
You don't need to rush, but please don't forget my little errand.nnDrop off the report on your way east. Thanks, traveller!
This would be going a lot better if our scouts weren't missing. nnOne of my men never returned from Narsis.
We'll head out of here shortly to help secure the path. nnI'll meet you on the other side!

With your help, we've managed to get a supply line running through Haven Trace.nnHopefully, we can get aid to Razorvine Refuge in time.nnYou should make your way there and see if you can help them out.
Never have so many Knights of the Flame fallen in a single battle. It's a tragedy.
<<1>> sent you? How sweet!
What do you want?
Keep that sample safe. Only give it to <<1>>!
Can I help you with something? nnI'm very busy right now. Digging through this muck takes a lot of work.

My father told me you found my note. Thanks for coming here to tell him.nnI managed to escape, but I still appreciate it.nnOne hope sustained me: that if I was killed on that dark day, a good person like you would bring my final message to my father.
Please deliver that message to Warguard M'zadha, south of here.
The Battlereeve is wise to suggest we fall back. However, the warmaster is determined to reclaim Haven, not retreat from it.nnM'zadha will see that this message reaches Warmaster Rahira.

Take those bags. Toss them in barrels around the port.nnYou know what I love about giving gifts? You always get something in return.nnWe're going to give them a big surprise, and we're going to get some entertainment!
J'Hriss will inform the Altmer about the maps.nnThis explains how they held an advantage over us when they attacked. They knew exactly where we would be!
It looks like my day is getting better and better. nnWhat do you want?
First, it was Argonian hunters and crocodiles. Now it's daedra! You'd think I've seen it all now!
My cousin died. My family decided that it is too dangerous to take his remains to Stonefalls. Like many others, they're taking him to the Velothi Rivergraves. nnNothing good can come of this.
The dead pose no threat to their enemies. Be still like the rock and be easily overlooked.
I'm certainly not a Daedraphile. nnMost of us are soldiers who were quickly trained by Vonov Sarturus. nnWhatever he's doing, that's the real threat. Capturing Haven was only a distraction.
You've done much for us, <<1>>. It's rare that a stranger impresses me.

You deserve the honor of recovering the power source for the Obelus. nnGo get it! Then I'll teleport you out of these tunnels, away from all these cultists.nnThere's probably a flaw in that plan, but I'll think about that later.nnYou go first.
Just let me catch my breath and I'll deliver news of the attack on Dunkarn Haven to the Queen.
Hurry through the portal! Destroy the sacred relic!
You're my savior, <<1>>! nnMarayn would have had my head if I left town, no matter what the cause. nnShe's a tough mistress, that one. Lucky me.

You have discovered much by questioning the courier within the glen. That is more than I've accomplished, though not from lack of effort.nnThe position of House Dres is most troubling, for more reasons than you know.nnKeep safe until we meet again.
I thought I saw a Warguard sneaking about a moment ago. Are the Warrior Guard near?
If I've guessed correctly, your quarry is downstairs. nnWe will meet again.
We cleaned up behind you. nnFew of us would have been brave enough to enter that portal like you and Rahira did.
Things are settling down. Soon, we'll best these filthy ogres.
I saw you went into the mines, and came out with the stench of goblin.  What news do you have?
I walked down here to get away from my parents. They're always arguing.
Some fools doubted the Warmaster. nnShe led us to victory, despite impossible odds.nnWe are unstoppable!
The village can be repaired. nnYou saved our families and friends. That's what really matters.
What have you found, traveller?
I'm awake! I'm awake!
It's not a long walk. Please, let's continue. I'm feeling weak.
What are you doing here? State your business!
House troubles are not our troubles. If they wish to destroy each other, then so be it. We will sift through the pieces once the dust has settled.
Keep to the roads. nnDespite our best efforts, the land is overrun with bandits, witches, and wild creatures.
The village can be repaired. In fact, we'll improve it! nnWe'll reinforce as much as we can. We'll learn from this struggle!
Villagers are trapped in their homes!
Slaughterfish. Slaughterfish everywhere.
Not calling you a liar, mind you. People have been seeing strange things of late. If you did see old Arnoit Sidrey, you wouldn't be the first.nnGives me the shivers, it does.
In all the months I've been posted here, you're the first traveller I've seen.

When you find my father, please tell him to hurry home! It's dangerous out there when you're all alone, you know?nnMaybe I'll make dessert while I'm waiting. Perhaps some thunderbug jam? nnMmm. Delicious jam.
Godrun has stepped down? I hope Borkul will allow me to return home to my family.
Gorvaro sent you to rescue me?
I have prepared a teleportation spell for myself. nnI will rest briefly, then leave quickly.nnI do not want to stay here another minute.

You can use the leaky bucket or borrow the one in the forester's camp up the hill. It's up to you.nnIf you're going to use the leaky bucket, then you'd better hurry once it's full. It leaks like a sieve.
Hello again <<1>>.
I'm headed east into Haven Trace! nnYou should join me. We could certainly use someone like you.
If you follow the beach north, you'll see a small encampment in the distance. That's where you'll find <<1>>.nnI'll continue scouting from here.nnWhen you find Cruor, make him pay.
Maybe I can squeeze in one last drink before I leave....
I heard a rumor that you killed the Great Spider herself! Now that's a job well done!
I'm sorry, I can't be bothered at the moment. Propylon readings are a hard study and I can't afford interruption.

This'll be a tale to tell! nnHere I am! Locked up... waiting for Imperials to feed me to bears... and then a valiant adventurer bursts forth to rescue me!nnSay, do you want to know who has the "kee"? It's on one of these guards, I'd warrant.

This'll be a tale to tell the boys! nnLocked up by Imperials... waiting to be fed to bears... until a brave adventurer burst forth onto the scene to rescue me!nnDo you want to know who has the "kee"? One of these guards, I'd imagine.
Would you like to try these on? nnThey feel much different than rope bindings, I assure you! nnDifferent, but... well... better!
What? How? nnOh, right. The book.
He's waiting for us in the other room. Let's not keep him.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! And that must be the Balac!nnWell go on, I don't know what's to be done with it. Give it to the old man.
The Imperials must learn from the mistake they made by attacking the Khajiit.

M'zadha is frail and thinks too much. He should carry J'raka's weapons instead of complaining.nnJ'raka is expected to stay here and wait for orders, but so many Imperials walk upright, not screaming in agony!nnJ'raka is truly being tested this day.
Ah, you have come, it is well! But where is Lyris? Has she abandoned the cause at last? No, no. That cannot be, it is not written so.nnGo find our Titanborn. Bring her here.

<<1>> does not agree with Farah being here!nnThis one thinks she's putting herself in danger. Farah is no warrior, not like <<1>>. nnThis one will make sure she returns home, where the Dominion can protect her.

Those obelisks are more powerful than I realized. I'm going to have my work cut out for me leading the mages out of here. No Imperial stands a chance of crossing the marsh.nnWho would have thought there'd be so much power in such tiny stones?

You have succeeded! The wards are active. We can make our way out of this thrice-damned marsh!nnI have never been more pleased to have Bosmer scouts by my side.nnMiscalculations were made when we evaluated our capacity to navigate this forest.
<The lost Altmer mage lies in a more peaceful repose than before. It is only a matter of time before the forest claims the body.>
Your aid is certainly appreciated.nnThese Bosmer do not seem to understand the need to prune unruly vegetation.
What if the Daedra were just a distraction? nnSuppose they were just a means of slowing us down so Vonov could complete his evil rites.nnJust a thought.
Hurry through the portal. Destroy the sacred relic.

I'm guessing the lost Altmer mage has already gotten killed in the forest. Wisps aren't kind, especially when you've got magic.nnThe ritual book he'd been carrying would probably be pretty useful to the Altmer to the north, though.
Return to Haven through the portal. nnRahira will meet you there.
I feel like I'm on fire.nnEverywhere... burning....nnPlease, make it stop.
I heard what you did for the injured. We all appreciate it. nnSaving a stranger's life today might mean life or death for all of us tomorrow.

Normally, I'd ask the guards to assist with this, but there are far too few of them. nnIf the Imperials attack Razorvine, we'll need all the defenders we can muster.nnI can't thank you enough for helping us.
Never fear, father. nnThis young <<1>> will find the rest of you in no time. I really do wish you'd stop running off, though!nnYes? Oh, it's you again, stranger! How goes the search?
You know, there are enough of us out here to overwhelm them.nnWe should break in and take the cure.
You should check to the east. The Imperials are occupying Haven now.nnRa'Vashi knows they have many weapons. Bring some to this one, so he may learn to fight!
Please respect my daughter's privacy. She's not feeling well.
The netchling wriggles from your grip.

We've unlocked a remarkable resource here, traveller.nnThe Dominion could use this area for storing our army's materiel. That should help us advance further onto the mainland.nnYour intervention has been invaluable. We extend our gratitude.

Don't worry about me. I'll sneak past those creatures to Thistlewhip's camp.nnIn the meantime, you should go find the Jaqspur.nn I suspect they're in the part of the forest our legends refer to as the Thrambleheart.
Does the <<1>> want something from me?
This one is quite amused by the madness you have sown!nnWere you inclined to sow some more, it is said that the Imperials have also headed to the east. Find them, and you will create trouble aplenty.
This one always thought the worst part about slavery was the whipping. nnNow Lady Vallis is too busy for whipping.nnSee? Things are looking up.
I want to go home.

If I killed every kwama in this place, I bet Lady Vallis would reward me.nnI've heard her rewards are very "ample." If you know what I mean.nnYou know. "Rewards." Get it? Huh?nnYeah. Her rewards on are her chest.
Could you convince the Lady to let us leave?
I doubt that monster would have let you escape with the Jaqspur.nnOnce we deliver this meat to Razorvine, I'm going to rally a group together.nnWe're going to slay that beast.
You should never trust a stranger... especially me! nnYou just drank a cup of poison! nnDon't worry. I'll give you the cure... if you can find me. Let the chase begin!
No need to thank me! nnIt's my pleasure to host such an exciting game.
Were you able to find where the corpses are going?nnI can't imagine there's anything to the phantom corpse cart rumor, but you never know....
The creatures worked together. They barked and chittered at each other, like they were talking.nnWhere we ended up, I don't know, but I was sure we were doomed.
The Grahtlord is too ancient to remember any ties it had to the Bosmer. Anything that old has to be dangerous. nnThis day, you demonstrated courage and fair judgement.
I was consumed by bloodsport, by the thrill of combat. Now, I wonder why I fought so hard for so little.nnI think my gladiator days are at an end.
You have something for a Perroult? I am Jeraine Perroult.
You've saved our livelihoods! Thank you so much!
I won't forget the loss of my family, but I can't just sit around and weep.nnYou've helped me get a start again. Thank you.
Thank you for checking on Golleon. nnHe didn't appear to be capable of fending off the Daedra on his own.
Thanks for doing this. I'm really terrified of trolls.nnMy brother was eaten by one, you know. I was only five years old, but I remember. I'll always remember.
No, I won't reconsider. nnLluthyne expects us to put our lives at risk for animals? nnI'd rather work the docks than get gutted by a poacher.
Give Lluthyne my love, won't you?
My friends are free. Thank you! Just promise me you'll stop the Singer before she harms anyone else.
You'll find my farmhands roundabouts the other farm buildings. Don't take any guff from them either! I'm sure one of those louts saw something suspicious.
Thank you for fetching a new sage for us! nnMany sunsets to you.
Oh goodness! I didn't mean to push him over. But he was... and I just....nnPlease, don't kill me. It was an accident!
We're depending on you to help stop the daedric threat. Don't let us down.n nSeek out daedric gates around Bangkorai, destroy them and return the sigil stones to me.
This may be a simple contract, but the honor of the Fighters Guild is at stake. Don't screw it up.n nCollect pendants, rings, patches, and pins from the bandits and return to me.
My patients will be anxiously awaiting news about the ritual.nnI can only hope my help will be enough to save their loved ones.
This disease, this plague... it came from Orcs. They are not like us, Daggerfall Covenant or not!nnIf my son dies, I will kill any Orc I see. His blood will be on their hands!
Hurry back to Wyress Reinette!
There's no reason for me to remain in Evermore now. My husband, my daughter, my brother... all dead.nnIf I stay, I'll die as well. You should leave before it's too late for yourself, too.
Those barbarians... they came back. Attacked us again. I knew it wasn't the trolls!

Giren! Trying to escape again? Someone needs another beating.nnLeave him with me. He's another feeble-minded slave. Bad teeth. Not the sort anyone of status or standing should possess.nnYou are of standing, yes? Maybe you should show me your teeth...
We're going to do well together, mark my words.
My children! nnHave you seen my children?
I have to find my family. nnI can't leave without them!
The Nereid is playing with more power than she can handle. We thank you for your help.
My master does not forget those who serve him, as long as their loyalty is absolute.
No doubt Bakar told you many lies. I am glad you saw him for what he was.
You can find the ingredients I requested out in the forest. Please hurry. Princess Elara's condition grows worse with each passing hour.
The dungeon entrance is behind the castle's eastern edge.nnYou must give the Queen's Letter of Release directly to one of the dungeon guards beside its entrance.
They've tied me to this infernal post!nnUntying me shouldn't be hard.
What's this? A letter from Her Majesty?nnI wish she'd send us some help against the ghosts in this dungeon.

Oh my! I didn't expect him to be the bandit.nnI know we'll have our forest back soon enough, but... Darkins? Where in his right mind did he even learn to summon like that? nnWell, I guess it serves him right!
I didn't think I'd see you again.
Even if it smells of sulfur and ash, the air outside that cage is more pleasant than the air inside it.
I know there are ghosts throughout this dungeon. Let's avoid battle where possible so that I may return quickly to Her Majesty's side.
Why would Her Majesty send us a letter? Is the page sick?
I hear the ancient whispers. You have retrieved my tomes.
Sorry to run off like that. nnI didn't want to stay out in the open any longer.

The creatures stalking the forest floor aren't the only dangers here. nnPerched high atop the trees, other creatures feed on the grubs... and anything else they can pounce.nnI'm sure you'll be fine, though.
We need to keep an eye on things. Her Majesty's been so worried about Princess Elara that preparations for battle are not proceeding as quickly as they should.
Constable Myn told me you pledged to make these Reachmen pay for their crimes. Have you helped us get our revenge?
Be wary when you approach Bravosi Dres, friend. nnI do not know his motives, but clearly, he has no conscience.nnAny creature who would leave others to die in such a place is reprehensible.
Relief at last! nnMay Vivec bless whoever thought to make this. nnPerhaps I can finally close my eyes and get some rest.
Please, find my sister. Let her know I'll be okay. nnI'll wait for her back in Elden Root. nnHopefully, she'll still have the lucky cape I left behind!
Do you have an appointment scheduled? If not, I really must insist that you leave immediately.nnEvermore's afflicted by a strange malady and as its Minister of Health, I am terribly busy.
The Minister of Health hides in his house. He thinks staying by his fire will keep him from this dreadful sickness.nnMeanwhile, Evermore's citizens are dying and disappearing.

We don't plan to stay here long. nnI don't know what brain fever they caught, but I won't see my family afflicted with it.nnThe temple will surely shelter us. Meet me there when you've done what must be done.
That note! I'm not sure if it got to my family in time.nnI must hope they're still alive. nnHope is all I have left.
Blessings upon you, friend, for what you have done for these people.
The battered spriggan has stopped moving.

I will not ask you to attack my fellow Reachmen, but their vile creations are an affront to every teaching of Reach magic. You shall destroy the Bloodthorn creatures, and I shall pray for their wayward masters to remember the true ways of the Reach.
There is no time to waste. Warn King Eamond at Bangkorai Garrison!
It is done.
I know there's a cure to this awful disease. I've seen the Reachmen using it. May Stendarr blind me if I lie!

I worked hard on that potion. It contains the distilled essence of several herbs and...nnWhat are you doing? You're trying to trick me into telling you my secret! Oh, no! I won't tell!nnYou just go to the farm and pour that into the well. You'll see!
<The spirit glares at you. You sense its annoyance.> nn<An image of <<1>> hunting on the south side of Branglebracken flickers in your mind.>

I know single combat seems an odd way to solve a tax dispute, but its use goes back generations in Evermore. Some say it's barbaric, but I couldn't do away with it even if I tried.nnWell, then, what was the outcome? Who won?

You've got the stone. The house is right over there, but it's well-guarded. No problem for you I'm sure.nnOnce you manage to get inside, look for a convenient desk or cabinet to hide the listening stone in - then get out.
Do you champion the cause of these tax evaders?

Single combat is quick and fair, so long as both parties agree to it. And since Captain Celd's agreed to our custom, it's all or nothing.nnI hope you excuse me; I don't feel well, or I'd undertake this fight personally.

I've agreed to their single combat rule, but I don't have to like it.nnStill, it's a lot quicker than trying to appeal unfair taxation through the courts.nnThere'll be no hard feelings no matter which side wins.
If we have to pay their taxes, none of us will get paid this trip. Who'll feed my family if I don't get paid?
Are you the champion for Evermore?
It seems I must wait outside with the common rabble. nnI will certainly bring this up to the high priestess in Iliath the next time I travel to Kragenmoor. nnThis will not stand.
The witchmen from the Reach have never paid respect to the call of nature. They must find a way to twist nature to their will.nnYou've shown them that the wyresses also know brute force.
Okay. I'll burn those poor bodies. You watch my back. Ready?
Of course I'm mad at him! nnWhen I get back to Elden Root, no tree will be high enough to hide him from me. nnHe'll wish those lurchers tore him apart!
I don't object to paying our fair share of taxes, but he was asking for nearly seventy percent of our profit. That's robbery, not a new tax.

I know single combat seems an odd way to solve a tax dispute, but its use goes back generations in Evermore. Some say it's barbaric, but I couldn't do away with it even if I tried.nnWell, then, what was the outcome? Who won?
I offered to fight for our rights, but the captain told me to stand down.
We've been placing bets on the outcome ever since you came aboard. I really hope you win!
I think single combat is a stupid way to see who's right and who's wrong.nnIt only proves who was luckier that day.

Do you think me callous? Cruel? nnIt's a useful image to cultivate. The more the afflicted think I'll kill them, the fewer of them I'll need to kill.nnI don't need their love, but a lack of respect from them would doom my people.
Come back tomorrow! nnBe sure to bring friends. The more the merrier!
Rahira greets you with dire news.
Most intriguing.nnThis is a rare collection of reagents. I am delighted to accept your gift.
War is no fun when you've got guard duty in a secure area. nnBy the time I'm sent to the front, all the Imperials will be dead!
The safety of the Thalmor requires my full attention. nnI have no time for conversation.nnKindly move along.
Their Royal Highnesses are gone now. I can't discuss the details of their departure, either.nnGood day.

My people's cries were met wit silence, despite the promises of the Ebonheart Pact.nnSuspicions and prejudices followed us. With the advent of this disease, I thought the rift would never be breached.nnNow that I have Redoran's ear, we will fix that.
Pray for those who perished in fury.nnAnd pray for those here now. They must complete the tasks of those who are gone.
Gods! Out of the frying pan and into the fire, it seems! nnHold your breath when you walk past those wretches. nnWho knows how this accursed sickness is spread!
I'm told you defeated an Omen of Vaermina.nnI pray that Count Hosni recovers quicly.

It seems the crows have departed from Evermore, but the black cloud hasn't. With Bangkorai Garrison taken, there's nothing stopping the Imperials from marching here.nnI didn't retake the throne to watch the kingdom fall though. We'll find a way.
You've come upon me in mourning, I'm afraid. Several members of my father's family recently passed away due to the illness within the city.nnWhat can I do for you?
Ah, sweet relief! After all that, I need to sit a spell.
So Gavendier sent you? Finally! Another voice of reason.
I hope you can find my daughter. nnRumors of House Redoran rebuilding the town have renewed my hopes.nnI hope she's still alive.

I spoke with our Ashlander captive before I let him leave. nnHe was as grateful as an Ashlander could be towards House Dunmer. He also said he would speak on our behalf with <<1>>.nnWe might finally be able to come to terms and rebuild Senie.
I'll keep these harnesses with me. nnWe'll try to rebuild our herds next season. We'll pass these on to the next generation.nnSo has it always been under sun and sky!
The box! You have returned my box.
I wonder. nnDid the scamps cause the mountain to erupt, or did the eruption cause the scamps to appear?nnI guess it doesn't matter, as long as we're doomed.
I hope the Minister is all right. They locked her up elsewhere in this horrible place.
The shrine of Boethiah lies along the road northwest of our conclave.nnSpeak with <<1>>. He allows pilgrims access to the shrine.
Seek out the books of ancient lore around Bangkorai, collect them, and return to me.

I wish you could have seen Erena when she was alive.nnHer skin was smooth as cream. Her eyes wer soft and warm. My moments with her were the happiest times of my life.nnI cannot live with her not knowing how much I care. Please, you must find her!
Please, travel north to Karthdar Pilgrimage.nnYou must speak to an Altmer named Tyl Eloren.
Those amulets should prove sufficient for your needs. nnShould you uphold your part of the bargain, our business will be concluded. nnTake them back to your army, and may Meridia guide your path.
What is it, child? What is that you hold?
We cannot leave Tamriel. We are bound here by Father Ergend's folly.nnFree us to move on.
I can't go home. The graveyard is overrun with undead. Soldiers from a battle down south...nnI think I'm going to be sick.
I'm so sorry - please forgive my manners. I'm not feeling quite myself.

Thinking clearly is becoming more difficult. nnI can hear my family crying in the night. Sometimes, I sense their presence behind me, but when I turn around.... I am alone.nnI don't think I have much time left.
I'll stay here until the Ashlanders share their cure. What choice do I have?
Why do we wait for the Ashlanders' mercy? nnWe should force them to share their cure with us!
I'm counting on you to pull your weight around here. Don't let me down.
I don't like Daedra, but I like dying even less. nnIf Boethiah can cure me, I'll gladly pledge my loyalty.nnI'm leaving for the Ashlanders' shrine tomorrow morning. It's just to the west, isn't it?
I offered the spirit my help, and now he needs us! Please, speak with him and see what can be done.
I know why you take these flowers. You think it a simple task. But this matter is greater than you can imagine!
You have returned. Were you successful? Are our crypts safe?
Wyress Reinette lives near the center of Evermore.nnI can only hope my petition reaches her before it's too late for me.
I'd much rather miss out on a few shipments than lose everything to bandits. nnThat just makes financial sense.
You have done good work. Once you defeated each spirit, it was cast below once more, woefully weak. It will not escape again.

This is a temporary respite for the Kagesh. nnThey have defeated my ordinators, but soon, the temple will dispatch more of them.nnOf course, I will be relieved for my incompetence. Looking at the wounded around this camp, I wouldn't contest that.
Does the wood seem brighter to you? It's like a fog lifted, but I didn't notice until it was already gone.
Any luck catching one of those cliff racers?
These men and women were my comrades. I trusted them with my life. nnIf I can't offer them this peace, then I have betrayed them.
My brother never gives up. nnI told him to wait for reinforcements from Davon's Watch, but he wouldn't listen.nnI hope he's still alive.

Maddened soldiers are roaming the grounds, attacking anything in their path. nnTheir minds are addled. They're little more than beasts.nnOne of them took the supplies from my hands. Then he wandered off and left me for dead. You've got to find them!
If these undead aren't dealt with quickly, they could march into Bangkorai.
You brought the body parts? Good. nnWe can perform the ritual as soon as this troublesome priest steps aside.
We cannot allow these men to raise King Eamond. I will not budge on this issue.
I'm not sure which is worse: being stuck out here or being posted in Davon's Watch to guard the cordoned district.nnI think I'm going to be stuck out here until I'm old and gray.

As if we needed another reason to fear those beasts! nnWhatever madness they brought with them obviously infected our soldiers.nnI sitll don't know how it spreads, though. Are we all as damned as the lost souls outside?
You could have just walked away. nnI was going to find my children. nnWe were going to have a good life.
You made a wise choice, <<1>>. I promise, I will do all I can to aid Bangkorai against these Imperial invaders.
In place of a strong sword arm, you chose a woman's skirts. I pray you did not make the wrong choice.
The Divines will never forgive this act of blasphemy. You made the wrong choice.
If we do not heed the Wise-Woman's tales of our ancestors, we will repeat their mistakes.
Hear the words of our Wise-Woman, and accept their truth.
Release me! Quickly!
If you hadn't come, I'm not sure what those Ashlanders would have done to me.
I'll have to swing by Norus' tent once I've finished going through these supplies. nnLet's just say I was less than kind when I thought he answered my inquiry about supplies with a joke.
