I almost don't know where to start. nnIt's been so long since I had real supplies!
I hope the supplies will last us for awhile.... Between the Orlishkaarn and Mt. Senie, it's a wonder we have anything left.
I think it best if we just leave poor Benjamin in the woods until this whole Reachmen mess blows over. Don't you worry! I'll be sure to check on him before too long.
I am no feminine mer of House Dunmer! nnMy heart is bound to the life of my tribe. nnMy soul has been pledged to serving Boethiah.
The women of the Houses are like pools in the waste. Fair to see, but no deeper than a finger-span. And poison if imbibed.nnA good Ashland woman is worth a dozen of them.
I've got my eye on you. Remember that.
While you bear the aspect of Hircine, none of the Daedric Prince's Huntsmen will attack you.
All I have is yours to use.
Someone dropped a weather-beaten journal near a battered chest.
The book is blank, and many pages have been torn out.
The book is blank, and many pages have been torn out.
WARRANT FULFILLED:  Melur the Rat, by <<1>>
The cage latch is securely locked. It appears as if a key, possibly held by the nearby gaolers, would unlock it.
The gravestone reads "Here lies Elisa Helane, the flower of Camlorn. Devoted daughter. Loving wife."nnRaymond's ashes have settled into the dirt around her grave.
Footfalls shift the earth, sending shivering tremors through my roots. You have returned to me.nnHave you solved the question of my existence?

The pages you've collected seem to fit perfectly into the book. With everything in place, the meanings are coherent. Many details fill the pages exploring the aggressive turn of the once passive creatures - each note signed by an "<<1>>".

A stench, similar to that of soured food, fills the air when the coffin is opened. The rotted remains of what could only be a Dunmer are scattered and broken within the coffin.nnThe hands and head are still missing.
I should deliver the dead guard's letter to his wife, Alain, in the Wayrest Slums.
You dump the moon sugar into the teacup, which invisibly melts in the lingering tea.at the bottom.
Malacath, Daedric Prince of the exiled, can only be overcome with strength. This is the first lesson of the Dunmer people.
Molag Bal ever seeks to corrupt our people through his deceit. It is through cunning that we overcome him.
You hear the sound of the door being unlocked from the inside.
From inside, you hear the sound of the door being unlocked.
From inside, you hear the sound of the door being unlocked.
To know Sheogorath is to know madness. At every turn, he seeks to create chaos where there was once order. Be ever wary of his gilded tongue.
Mehrunes Dagon wars against us at every turn, with every step we take within Vvardenfell. Even the earth turns against the Dunmer people, but still we persevere.
The corpse of a miner lays bruised and caked in coagulated blood. Judging by the wounds, this looks to be the work of goblins.

This mostly illegible journal reads:nn"...While mining, we uncovered what appears to be a Daedric structure and artifact. Someone unknowingly activated the artifact, summoning a Dremora. He killed most of us.. by the eight I hope I get out of here."
The Daedric artifact hums idlely.
Your body feels tingly as you approach the propylon.
A letter sits on the table.  It looks recently written in a language you can understand.

"Days have been long and hard, but we're managing everything fine. Ore shipments have been on time and gems have been a nice bonus for us to line our pockets. I should have joined the miner's guild a while ago!"

"One of the night watches spotted a queer sight a couple nights back. Seems there were a couple goblins not far from the mine entrance. I normally wouldn't worry too much, but a large figure was with them, grunting some sort of nonsense."
The runes in the stone writhe, and settle on a language you can read:nn"Cormeir PrisonnnWelcome, Warden. Access to the prison is granted.nnUse caution when interacting with prisoners."
The only skulls I can offer him are ones from people who are already dead.nnHe was the aggressor here, not me.

We should be able to drive out the remaining Imperials, now that Calypsi is gone.nnI hate to think what would have happened if the Imperials had a fortress closer to Elden Root.nnI'll admit it. You've saved us, <<1>>.
What am I supposed to do with that creature you brought? nnDid the captain send you here to chase me off?
The Ashlanders sent a message for Ulden? Ha! He'll send them a message soon enough.
You look like you can handle yourself, but if you know what's good for you, you'll bring allies.
I'm glad you're on our side, <<1>>!
Just let me know, and I'll open the door for you.
Just a moment. nnBefore you go, tell me of our benefactor, <<1>>. Why does she risk sending us saltrice?nnThe ordinators would not look kindly on her if they knew.
If you find Tribune Marius, kill him  but don't fret if he's fled. nnOur real goal is hoisting the flag of Evermore again.
Kill their men. Burn their banners. Destroy their war machines.nnWe'll drive them from this garrison with their tails between their legs.
<<1>> forced me to let the Ashlander go. nnAfter a long discussion, she made me see how my anger was affecting my judgement.
Unleash me on the Imperial soldiers, <<1>>. nnI'll destroy them.
Have no fear, <<1>>.nnI'll focus all my healing powers on you.
Keep them distracted, <<1>>, and I will exploit every weakness you reveal.nnWe will destroy our enemies!
I'll distract them as best I can and make openings for you, <<1>>.nnLet's take back Bangkorai!
If the captain learned I disobeyed a direct order, I'd be in irons. nnHe hasn't given any orders to you, however.nnShow no mercy.
At least some people in this camp have sense. nnI just hope they keep their lawman dog away from me until they allow me to leave.
The woods weep with joy; they tell me Gurles finally moved on. I am glad for him, and glad you were able to help.

Thank the Divines! No one died in the attack, even though there were injuries on both sides.nnI'm being held hostage. They're going to trade me for the infected soldiers. nnI hope they can be cured before things go too far.
The longer you wait, the closer the fort's soldiers come to death.nnDelay, and their captors may kill them.nnWould you trade all their lives for the life of one prisoner?
Was that the sound of blades I heard?nnI hope this hasn't come to blows.
The Imperials will think long and hard before challenging us again.
There you are! Did Gurles tell you what he was planning? Did you know what he meant to do, when he sent you off to the Sentinel's statue?
If you can help Loraine out, I'm sure you can aid the soldiers who were injured in the attack.
Very well. You've collected the parts. nnTell Sir Dencent your decision, and it will be done.nnKing Eamond will stand once more, marching with his army to destroy the Imperials!
Did Tirinaat really grant you permission to enter her home? nnAn invitation to enter Wise Woman Tirinaat's yurt is a great honor.nnOf course, I doubt an outlander like you would understand that.

I know he didn't mean to do it, but one of the soldiers injured me while I was tending his wounds. nnI immediately knew what that meant.nnMy brother is a werewolf. Now that I've been infected, I've chosen to become one, too.
If we do not stem the tide of Dreugh, they will multiply.nnSoon, they will threaten the outskirts of Ebonheart.nnFor now, dealing with the spread of the coral growths is not as important.
With the newly lowered Dreugh population, now is the perfect time to launch our attack against the heart of that coral.
You found a glowing locket on a grave with a guild seal in Othrenis?nnI'll ask you why you were robbing graves later. First, let me see that.
The Prince's Shrine was only a tumble of bricks when we came to it. Now its glory begins to shine once more!
I have failed the Three. I've failed my comrades.

Most of my mates have grown mad throughout the centuries of undeath.nnStriking them down will not permanently kill them. nnIt will only cut them from their bodies for a short time, long enough for them to rest.
We've failed Boethiah. We failed our tribe.
I'm deciding which of the prisoners should be "killed while trying to escape."nnTough choice.
A severed head! How gruesome.nnThe Huntsmen approve!

If you would dare enter the grotto without an offering, prepare yourself for a brutal fight. nnThe skill of the Huntsmen is not limited to tracking beasts.nnIf you have an offering, do not hesitate to enter. Fortune favors you today!
You're back! And all your body parts are intact... I think.nnHow did it go? Can we get out of here before the gates of Oblivion open?

The polyps are our most precious gift from the coral. nnFrom them, the blessings of the sea may spread throughout this broken land.nnThe Dunmer would see them destroyed, but they're blind to its beauty.
Welcome, traveller! I've been feeling so much better since our little trip.
So much has happened ... so much tragedy ....nnI can barely think.
My vision fades.nnTell me, stranger, are those beasts dead yet?

I have to clean up this mess. nnThose Wood Orcs shouldn't find out about the Dominion's presence in Barkbite. They don't take kindly to outsiders, especially those who enter their sacred lands.nnGet to Garland as quickly as you can.
My friend, we've saved many lives this day.nnAll thanks to your aid, I should say!

I should chastise you for your escapades while the Camoran King watched through your eyes.nnHowever, he is healthier and happier than he has been in weeks. I believe he even made lewd overtures to a serving maid!nnPerhaps I should still chastise you.
I'm glad to see you made it out of the cave alive.

If we're going to have any hopes of finding Vonov, we'll have to destroy the obelisk. It's inside that cave.nnOnce its cloaking magic is down, I'll meet you on the other side of the tunnels.nnThen we'll finish this.

The entrance to <<1>> lies on the path north of us.nnPlant seeds in the blighted gnarls you find along the way... and be careful.nnThough the amulet you wear protects you from the miasmata, it won't protect you from the evils you encounter.
Well, that worked out better than I hoped. nnNow we just have to get out of here alive.

You're in over your head, <<1>>. nnStill, I won't be the one to question your motives. If you're seeking evidence of the corruption seizing our people, keep searching. nnWhen you find it, I'll tell you more.

The bonfires will keep us for another night. After that, who knows?nnThese fools need to get organized. They're too worried about vengeance, and they won't bother taking care of themselves.nnWell, if they won't, I guess we'll have to intervene.
Can you tell me where we are? nnWe've been moved around so much....
I wish I had more than this to wear. We weren't allowed much.nnIs the wind always this cold?
Rats can be tasty if you know how to cook them properly.nnThis one wishes there were more rats here.
So! This is freedom!nnThat's funny. This one feels just as hungry as she did before she was free.
I'm from Cheydinhal. Do you know it?nnIt's on the border between Cyrodiil and Morrowind.nnI can still remember standing before the Great Chapel of Arkay.

The ones who killed the masters don't have a plan. nnYes, we're free. We're also hungry, cold, and stranded in the middle of a country full of slavers.nnI don't understand. What do they think they've achieved?
Thank you again for delivering that letter.nnI've been waiting for a while.
Can't stand. Too dizzy.nnPlease, don't let the Imperials finish us off!
Wasafa and I grew up together.nnI have no doubt he's still alive.

If someone told me a stranger would arrive to change my outlook on this war, I would've laughed. Of course, after I told them to quit wasting my time.nnBut you've done it, I admit. You're the one asset we needed all this time.
I'm too injured to escape. I'll do what I can to care for any other peasants that the Reachmen capture. Thank you.
Use the key to the shackles, free the captives, and then report back here to me.
You've done us a great service here today, <<1>>.nnI can't thank you enough, especially for ensuring Josselin's safety.
Thank you for delivering this letter. nnI won't be able to respond to their requests for a while.nnStill, it's go to know what resources we'll need in the months to come.
Off with you, now. nnI've much to consider.nnOh, and tell the captain I will soon need more of his forces.
Hurry! Find the antidote before it's too late. Save my son!
I've heard you've done the camp a good turn here today. Hopefully, with the information you gained from that prisoner, we'll win this war yet.
<<1>>! I hope you can forgive me.
That food saved me from starvation, but I still don't have the strength to escape. Someday, I will. nnI'll just have to stay alive until then.

I can ensure you safe passage from my champions back to Motag's cave, but that is all.nnI will meet you there shortly... unless you flee. nnIf you flee, I will hunt you down and rip your limbs off, one at a time. Fair warning.
The crying stopped. nnYou did something, didn't you?
I don't know if you have the power to free us, but please try.
I heard your warning! I'll get out of here ... as soon as I can sneak past Malumud.nnYou're killing me. Do you know that? You're signing my death warrant.
Old Zad's in the back.nnHe's in a room on the way up to the Fallen Grotto.nnYou should see what he's doing.
Malumud and the others made it?nnI knew they would!
Hurry up and unlock me before it's too late.
Zhavas is happy to have her metal back.nnPerhaps living in a tree will do this one good, particularly if there are helpful strangers like you around her.
I should have listened to <<1>>. My sister suffered until the very end! nnSometimes the price of hope is too great. I wanted to believe a cure was possible.nnMy selfishness cost her too much pain.
Word of your arrest has reached me. I must apologize for my father.nnHe always told me, "If I wasn't wearing this crown, I'd be a terrible rascal!"
You'll always be welcomed and honored here in Ebonheart, <<1>>.
This disease attracts all sorts of unwanted characters.nnThe Rilvayn's were good friends of mine.nnI hate to see their property defiled by such filth.
Greetings, <<1>>.nnHave you seen my spineless son recently?nnI'll go free him when there's a break in the fighting.
Knowing my mother is safe will surely make my suffering easier to bear.nnThank you, <<1>>.
Did the Commander send you? I just stopped for a moment to catch my breath.
Are you here to torture me? You don't look like the type.
<<1>> will figure it out.nnShe'll know what to do.nnShe must!
<<1>> was injured capturing our friend here.nnShe's waiting for a healer outside the sentry tent at the camp's southern edge.

By Mauloch, King Eamond was a good leader. Strong, fierce, and bold. He fought as well as any Orc.nnHe deserves a better tribute, but I haven't the tools or forge I need.nnI made this with copper scraps I found around the camp.
You have cleared the contract board. That is most excellent.
You are brave to enter our village so brazenly... or perhaps you're irredeemably foolish.nnRegardless, I'll hear what you have come so far to say.nnThen I'll order my guards to kill you.
It's rare to see a stranger willing to take the time to help others. nnEbonheart is lucky to have you here.
You gave the saltrice to the Ashlander Farseer? nnDid she say anything about me? No?nnNo cure? Maybe I just haven't earned it yet. Maybe I need to do more.
Omaynia would be the best place to check.nnHouse Dres occupies most of that town. They have their fair share of Breton slaves.nnI hope it won't take much to get him back.
"A friend" indeed.
Should we document what happened here or leave it hidden to history?
Shaviri has no one to trust. nnRedguards fear and hate magic.nnYou are Shaviri's only hope to keep what's inside the chest from getting out.
Hurry up and unlock me before it's too late.

I must gather reagents to commune with the coral-child.nnThis conflict will not be resolved with steel, but by the will of the coral itself.nnGo to the heart and find out what occurred. I will follow when I am ready.
Truly, Muqaddim proves the weakness in fleshlings. His motives are nothing short of typical  quite predictable!
Like you, I am a warrior.nnMy once valiant acts are now construed as villainy!nnTruly, the law is a fickle mistress.

The curse is gone, thank Stendarr. I hope I wasn't too delirious in our previous encounter.nnNow I get to focus on the wounds Dremora left behind. It's a good thing the finger he took wasn't on my main swordhand!
I think that did it. Take it to Captain Renoit.nnThen tell him not to come back.
I'll return this to Evermore and explain how it's made.nnThen I'll return to Kerbol's Mill to make amends for our attack.
I hope you and Moric found something I can take back to Evermore.
Be ready for anything, <<1>>.
I'm going to end up as a sacrifice. I just know it!
You've gathered enough to heal many people.

You can find Bralyn wandering the markets. nnAldyne is probably wasting the rest of her fortune at the Ebonheart Inn.nnGaven never leaves the docks.nnThey all owe me a significant amount of coin. Be discreet, but forceful.
So Kerbol believes he can prevent my soldiers from becoming werewolves? If that's true, I'll consider it a gesture of good will.
Please, save these people, if you can.nnThey cured my brother and took us in when no one else would.
Ferise and I go back a long time. I'm a bit hurt she thought I would not understand. I will have to buy her something nice to celebrate.
I will convince the coral-child to pacify the Dreugh.nnThe bulbous polyps are numerous. They shouldn't be hard to spot.
Raiyad is a friend, and I trust him. He will not lead you wrong.
Ha ha ha! Ow!
I know Janise is probably dead, but some small part of me can't stop hoping she's alive.
I heard soldiers assaulted Kerbol's Mill! nnDid you say Barnabe's all right?

First, a slave revolt. Now the tragic news about Serjo Belaal....nnI suspect there are hidden Daedric influences behind these untimely events.nnIf it's not the Daedra, it's got to be the Altmer... or maybe....
We can only pray that Serjo Belaal has the grace of the Three.
Those supplies were my way out of this cursed, disease-ridden land. nnNow I may never have enough of them to start over in Deshaan.
Will you meet Rahira in the Thalmor? nnFrom Razorvine Refuge, follow the road northwest to Elden Root. nnThe Thalmor is southwest of the Elden Tree.
I should have known something like this would happen sooner or later. nnAnd the guards do nothing? nnThey've made it quite clear what they think of us.
Ala told me what you did. nnForgive me for not trusting you, but it's hard to know who's a friend these days.
I'll trust you to deal with the archmage, <<1>>.nnYou look like you can handle yourself.
I'm sure they've taken the medicine to the warehouse district north of here.nnThey won't take kindly to strangers in the area.nnBe on your guard.
I'll make my way out of here, don't you worry. You get on your way; I'm tough as bark and twice as stubborn. You've done a great thing here, my friend.
I don't have to bring the food upstairs now. I'm not going to get ea....nnUh, never mind. They still listen. I can still be killed.nnStay away from me!
What Ovis must have thought of me all this time!nnI hope he'll see reason and speak with me.
"Aunt Heba" and I will be moving on soon. It's too dangerous here. nnWe're still very grateful for your help.
The entirety of our Great House is in mourning after Serjo Belaal's cruel murder.nnHer loss is a source of great sorrow to us.
Gargolyes harry me constantly, but that's better than toiling under an Imperial lash.
I spoke to the captain after you left. He was more than willing to help, after the good turn you gave him.nnThe traitor is well within our grasp.
One does not keep the tribal elders waiting.
Another has come before us, one who has done much for our people.nnUfa did well to send you.
I don't suppose you have any food? nnThere's less out here than in the slave camp.nnDon't you think that's odd?

The powder I gave you should dissolve easily on the guard's rations.nnIf you hurry, you can make it there before the next shift change.nnLet me know when you've done the deed. We can make our way out together!
I need you to bring Redguard corpses to the graves my disciples have prepared.nnI'll meet you there.
Tell <<1>> that I tried.nnI almost made it.nnAlmost ....
The slaves you freed are now mingling with the rebels around town.nnWe're still arranging for their transport back to Black Marsh.
I'll never forget how you helped me cleanse the Imperials' desecration at the Bone Fields.
I must have a few words with Sera Thovasi before I begin my journey to Mournhold. The families wish to settle their accounts with him as soon as possible.
So it's true. The Dres buy and sell us like grubs.nnI would've liked to be surprised.
I grow my ingredients myself. nnIt's not easy anymore, not with the affliction and the eruptions of Mount Senie and Mount Thendr.
Fort Virak lies north of Omaynia, veering a bit west.nnIt guards the entrance to the rift.
Poor thing. She really needs more water than we have around here.

Father doesn't let me go outside often. He's afraid the slaves will harm me.nnI - I'm afraid of the slaves, truth be told. But they've been very polite to everyone in our House. When we say we're Redoran they back off and wish us a good day.
House Father Aryon says we should leave the rebel slaves alone. nnYou know what? We did. Then they burned down half the buildings in town.nnHow long will it be before they come after us?

The Dres say other races need to be freed from oppressive rulers. They must be taught our ways.nnBut that's pure xuth, as the Argonians say. They just need slaves to work their saltrice plantations. Slaves make the Dres a lot of money.
My child! My son! What has fate done to you? nnWhy have you left me alone in this world?nnHe walks sightless no more. Did you murder him, or had he died long ago? nnI am... so tired.

A lot of people out there talk about their lives before they were enslaved.nnThat's great for them, I guess. I don't have much to go back to.nnMy village could have been rebuilt by now, but I saw everyone I knew killed or carted off in chains.
Would you care to join me in a psalm to Vivec? It's said he wrote it himself!nnIt's all about the divine power of his "milk finger"... whatever that is. nnWho can fathom the forms a god may take?

If you're travelling about the grounds by night, you might think you see House Mother Aryon. nnYou might think you've seen her leaving her manor for the stables. nnI assure you, you see no such thing.

I'll miss my conversations with Serjo Belaal. Hers was the only mind of quality in this forsaken hovel.nnIf I ever find the filthy n'wah who arranged her murder, I can assure you their screams will be long and loud.
Your face says it all.nnThank you. Now I know.
Did she ever truly love me? Was it all a game to her? nnI couldn't bring myself to make the first strike.nnShe seemed to attack me with ease.
Get out of here! You'll bring them all down on us!
When we fought the Imperials, every citizen of Hallin's Stand took up a sword.nnEvery citizen will do so again if they ever return.nnThis is a proud day.
Thanks to you, I'm back inside the walls of <<1>>! nnAnd I'm in my favorite bar! It's good to be back.

Greetings friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that. nnIf you want to join the guild, you should visit the Fighters Guild Hall in Daggerfall.
What's that I smell?
Seek out ancient lore around Stormhaven and return to me.
We're in your debt, my friend. nnHopefully, studying this book will give us more insight into the recent rise of necromancy in Stonefalls.
We're depending on you to help stop the daedric threat. Don't let us down.n nSeek out daedric gates around Stormhaven, destroy them and return the sigil stones to me.
I'll make my way west to the sulfur harvesting camp for safe keeping. nnMeet me there when you have enough unusual fire salts.
I hear many rumors in the halls of the Mages Guild.nnThat gate to the east may not be the only one. nnIn fact, it might not even be the only one in Stonefalls.
I'm not looking forward to telling my the buyer that I don't have his goods.nnYou were still planning on collecting those crystals, right?
Please, leave her that note! I can't face her after what I've done!
<You see the staff in the man's hand again. Somehow, it has returned.>nn<Looking closer, you could almost swear that the dead man is grimacing. His lips have curled into a disdainful sneer.>
If I had to guess, I'd say they're stuck near the base of those large figures. nnThey seem to be the source of all this trouble.
Thank you for delivering the message. nnWe are truly in your debt. I only wish there was a way we could properly repay you.
My head still feels a bit foggy.nnIt's as if I've been sleeping.
I feel so disoriented.nnFor some reason, I'm losing my voice.nnIt's as I've been screaming... for hours.

I predict that next week, the guards will mention a sudden drop in crime. nnI also predict the Captain of the Guard will claim it's due to her "proactive methods" and "get tough" attitude.nnWhat a clod.
As soon as reinforcements arrive, we'll charge into Gil-Var-Delle.
I don't have time to write Ogambu back, but thank you for your assistance.
I heard you survived what happened in Gil-Var-Delle, but I didn't think it was true. nnYou're the first one to emerge from that place alive since... well, since longer than any of us can remember.
I'm glad to see you're healthy. nnYou know, that girl was really odd.nnThank you again for the amulets. There should be enough to supply the Dominion's troops.
Those effigies could be anywhere. nnScamps seem to revel in looting the corpses here.
I'm so relieved to know they're all right. nnI've been imagining the worst for far too long.
I doubt the world will miss Irikeel. nnCertainly those who stepped in his leavings won't miss him.
Did you find out what was in those unmarked shipments? On second thought, I don't want to know. I'd rather stay out of House Dres' affairs.
<<1>> got the message to you. Good. I wanted to talk to you about your position here.
Yoon is glad to have met <<1>>.
You didn't have to search for me.nnFew would care to contemplate the regrets of a dead skooma addict.nnI certainly appreciate it.
You should leave this place immediately, before I throw you in irons.nnYou have no business meddling in House Dres' affairs!nnMind your tongue stays in your head... before someone removes it for you.
Let me know when you're ready to go to the statues. nnI have the power to take us there. No harm will come to you on your journey.
Ordinator Galen has been excessively pleased with himself lately. nnIt looks like his star is rising in the Tribunal Temple.
I heard a big commotion from that cave where the skooma peddlars gather. nnThere were Ordinators everywhere! nnI don't know if any lasting good will come of it, but we can hope.
"Cliff racer flies so high flyinnn' so hiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiigh!" nnHm? Oh, sorry. Old folk song from Vvardenfell. nnWhat can I get you?
Lately, I've had trouble telling if I'm asleep or awake. nnI'm afraid I might do something senseless if I leave with my family. nnI wouldn't harm them for anything.
After you've rested, return to <<1>>.
Our turns are finished.
<This ogrim appears trapped in place by magical bonds. Clearly there's someone behind this.>
It's simple. nnKill scavengers around the Bone Fields. There are plenty of opportunities to harvest vulture gizzards and lion hearts.nnThen return to me. I'll pay you well for them.
Will you be staying in Ebonheart long, serjo? nnI'm sure we could make your stay more pleasant.
Staying in Ebonheart long, serjo? nnI'm sure I could make your stay more pleasant.
I should have fought harder. I should have protected Master Muzgu.
Quickly! To save Stormhaven, I must die.
You there! Will you let your soul fall into the hands of Daedra?
None of these wasted souls will ever amount to anything. They are what they are. They will never be anything more.
Wh-what  ? Mother, is that you? I'm not ready to get up. Leave me alone  .

<You've found a dead body. This Dunmer recently met his death.>nn<Judging from his clothes, he was a farmer.> nn<A shovel beside him looks just like the one Faynis gave you. You aren't the first he's sent to get his father's fortune.>
Good luck to you in the games, stranger.nnYou're going to need it, heh.
Forget everything you've seen here.
Don't spare any concern for this one. He's misbehaved terribly. nnHe needs a firm hand. I'll give him the discipline he desperately needs.
Let's see. That was a carafe of shein, three bottles of mazte, one mazte bottle with a slice of gorapple, and a roast guar.
Investigate each cairn in Arlimahera's Grip and find my great-grandfather.

Seems like the Ordinators have finally put a dent in the skooma trade. nnPeddlars are still down in the Gutter, but they don't have much to sell. The addicts are getting desperate!nnNasty stuff, skooma. Never tried it myself, thank the Three!
House Brother Elbryon has found someone to fix the lamplights in the Gutter... again.nnSuch a waste of our money.
Istahn is by the eastern passage into the mining camp.
How did it go?
Kragenmoor is a Dres town. They'll never let you forget it, either.
Have you ever been over the Valus Mountains to the west? nnNibenay is on the far side. That's Imperial territory... or it was before the Imperials started fighting each other.
You risked your life to free us, friend. We're forever in your debt.
You'll find <<1>> near the altar.nnYou've got to save her before it's too late!
Help me get revenge for my suffering.nnKill any Reachmen you encounter and collect their belt knives for me.
I'm not leaving until the Imperials pay for all they've done.nnBe careful out there, <<1>>.
I don't know how they're training these things, but I'm going to find out.
You must hurry. The Imperials could find the sword at any moment.
I can't believe someone brought in Sewer-Tail before I could. nnI had big plans for that reward money!
If the Imperials have the sword, then we may be in very grave danger.

You're the one who relit the lamps, aren't you? nnI thought Elbryon's idea were the foolish theories of a scholar. Still, I have to admit it. Crime has been down recently.nnI'm grateful for anything that makes my job easier.
My apologies, sedura! I'm so sorry you had to notice me!
If you don't polish their chitin every day, they'll get depressed.nnThat's an old silt herders' secret, you know.
Our Great House is beset by ill news. nnFirst, it was the disapperance of Grandmagister Jaleyck.nnNow it's the death of House Father Teranos.

Just as Saint Veloth freed our minds from the decadent malaise of Summerset, each of us must set aside the distractions of daily life when we pray to the Three.nnWhenever we pray, our thoughts must be pure.
Still no smoke from Mount Heimlyn! nnI hope the mountain is placid now.
I'm certain the forbidden tomb holds the answers we need.nnI just hope you can find them.
The dreugh are thinning out, retreating.nnDid you succeed?
It's sacrilege to have the bodies of our honored dead rise again, their spirits enslaved.nnWe've got to stop this.
Are you listening carefully? Follow the signals exactly.nnIf you don't, our man inside will think something's wrong, and he won't reveal himself to you.
Do you have business here with our noble house? nnI'm the senior representative here. The Grandmagister is... missing. nnPatriarch Leyden has gone to Deshaan to find him.
The sun is shining. The insects are singing. The Dres are humilated.nnIt's a perfect day.
Have you travelled up the slave trading road that runs north through Omaynia? It's such a flyspeck of a village! nnHouse Father Aryon can keep it. So can his pathetic daughter.
Trust me when I say this is a matter of utmost importance. nnOh, and if the barkeep asks a favor of you in return, it would benefit you to oblige her.nnGot it? Good.
Brela works in the merchant square on the west side of Davon's Watch. She'll be expecting you.nnKeep your nose clean. If you fall in with the authorities, we won't be able to help you.
I expect great things from you, <<1>>.

We have no proof that House Dres is behind these latest atrocities, but all signs point to their involvement.nnTake those documents back to Dres.nnI'd love to see their faces after we find that proof.
The sacred oil is our finest.nnThe leaders of the Tribunal Temple in Mournhold blessed it personally!
Find the scroll that explains how to break the curse. nnPlease, set me and my men free!
Well, look who it is!nnMy dear friend, my wondrous rescuer, you've found me! What a lovely surprise.nnTell me, how have you been?

We were sent to repair the waterworks. We've came so far, all the way from Bthalag-Zturamz.nnMy brothers died in an accident. Can you help me now? nnSo many rely on our work. I'm so worried. I can't leave until it's fixed.
Hopefully, your sacrifice won't go unnoticed.

You! The letter-bearer. You should know my sister is dead.nnYou may have been the last person to see her alive.nnThat means you should be the first to know: I'm going to find the monster that killed her and take my revenge!

Each fire must be lit! nnI cannot light them. You may try, but the activation pedistal only lights one and not all, as it should. nnThe fires are bound together. Light them all, and the basement is open.
Find my experiment! Bring the pieces together....
I once trained students in summoning... and now I cannot even contain the weakend Daedra summoned by students. nnI must find an answer to why this is... and why I am here.

The spirit's warning is dire. We have heard travelers tales of giant anchors, with bands of Daedra nearby.nnI fear they tell the same story, and that the Mages Guild must use our might to destroy such anchors.
The pain twists my insides.nnI can neither eat nor sleep. nnHow much longer must I be forced to endure this agony?
Go to Mazira. We will join you soon.
You have my blades and many others.nnTell Mazira. Tell him we will fight.
No more words.nnTell Mazira my army is hers.
Legatus Verro will fall!nnThen the souls of our brothers and sisters will finally be free.
Everything is becoming hazy. Find the antidote to the poison before it's too late. I've heard it's in a crate on the other side of camp.
When you find him, do not harm him.nnI have many things I want to say and do before he dies.
I'm not sure where my bodyguards have gone.nnThey should be arriving any moment now.nnYou'll tell me if you see Sting-Lash about, won't you?
You'll understand when you get there. nnSo much suffering. It's more than any mortal should bear.nnI know my thoughts are blasphemous. I don't know how to stop them.

Travel east, through the ruins, and look for the raving Altmer. nnHe may be on the road leading to Elden Root, out of the ruins. nnIf you find something good on his corpse, please bring it back here! Share the wealth!
They call me a fool because I believe my wife will recover. nnShe may be sick, but she's far stronger than they suspect.
Oh, hello! Were you looking for me?
You are not permitted to leave until <<1>> is done with you.
Master Tree-Paws believes you will make a good forester.
You look excellent today, <<1>>.
Someday you may be a master runecrafter, <<1>>.
What have you there? Can it be?nnMy missing prize! nnHere, hand it over!
I was so sure. It all made sense.nnIf not the dwarves, who is to blame for our doom?
You haven't forgotten to bring a gift, have you?nnYou don't want to see me disappointed!
You found my devotion book?nnI thought I lost it when I fled.
"There are no current contracts for this Guild Hall. If you wish to act on more contracts immediately, please travel to the Narsis Guild Hall in Deshaan. They may have more work."
The prince is having us wait for two more squads of Aldmeri soldiers. nnWe need reinforcements, but the enemy will also have time to prepare for our attack.nnThis is a risky tactic.
You've done it! Verro is no more!
I'm lucky to be stationed here, where I can watch over you.nnI'll be the first to know when you've won.
Well fought. Stendarr guide you.
Omaynia is west of here, over the crags and rocks of the coral.nnThe path was treacherous, but well worth it.nnMy brother was always the faster on. I do not know how he could have fallen.
These are some fine shards. Oh! This one is breathtaking! nnWell done!
If you can bring me enough corn rose oil, I can show you how foresters use it. nnYou can draw the oil from the corn rose blossoms around Davon's Watch.
Once you bring me enough thin hides, I can show you what you can craft with them.
You have your task. Get to it.nnI need you to extract dioptase nuggets from the hills to the west, outside Davon's Watch.
All the guar-herders of the Kagesh know of your deeds. Our tribe is grateful. The gates of our village are open to you.
These rings force miasmata out of an infected body. nnIt will greatly aid our healers in restoring the wounded.nnThank you again, <<1>>. Many of our injured will survive, thanks to you.
I know it's wrong to send you in my place. I should do this. I just can't go, quickly, before it's too late. Do what you can!
Have you found <<1>> yet?nnI know she wouldn't just abandon the rest of the captives.

Once you get the keys, look for our scout up in the mushroom caps. He should know where to find our people.nnLook hanging vines you can climb, but be careful. The Imperials have been keeping a close guard on them.
Get back to the Thane and Broadleaf. Let them know what you've done.nnOnce... I recover a little... I'll be getting out of here myself.
Don't worry about me! No, no! I'm fine. I am! See? Can't you see?nnNo, no! Get the others! Free them and then find the scout! He... he will know what to do next.
Have you discovered anything of the Farseer? The quickest path to answers lies in the direction of the Temple. Good luck!
Those crystals will continue spawning elementals regardless of what happens with the rift. Have you had any luck getting rid of them?
This amulet you wear will protect you from the miasmata?nnYou seem sure of this... good luck!
I haven't seen <<1>> in a while. nnHave you? No?nnWell, that's a damned shame, isn't it?
My lady awakens - it's a miracle! You must speak with her at once.
More Ordinators will come, but we'll hold them off.nnMay Boethiah's will be done.
I cannot believe you chose me as Regent! I... I will do my best, I suppose. We always do our best.nnOh, I pray Queen Arzhela decides to rule again soon.
You have made the right choice, <<1>>. Under my guidance, Evermore's people will weather this storm.nnAll that I can do to keep them fed and safe, I will do.
It saddens me that we can do nothing for this <<1>>.nnHer fate lies in her own hands. nnIf she abandons the Tribunal's heresy and embraces Boethiah, however, he may show her mercy.
Warden Branchsinger is an excellent scout. He's got the eyes of a cliff racer and the instincts of a senche-tiger.
We heard how you helped the Warden Master. nnThank you. Our friends deserved better than undeath.
Keep them distracted, <<1>>, and I'll exploit every opening you reveal. I've got your back!
I need to get to Elden Root for more supplies. nnPlease, if you find yourself troubled by that Daedra's magic, find me. nnI can help.
Hurry. Travel southeast to Morwha's Bounty. nnWe need to know if the Withered Hand has struck again.
Follow the road west until you reach the pens.nnThe tribune or someone from her entourage will be waiting for you.

Splendid! You decided to join us after all!nnAfter the troubles we've encountered, I didn't think you would show... yet here you are!nnWe really need of your help. The ruins are infested with quarrelsome goblins.
It's a shame the rioting had to end so soon. nnThe clatter of swords, the crash of broken glass, the roar of angry drunks... it's enough to bring a salty tear to this old sailor's eye.

My dear <<1>>, these workers are intolerably disloyal to the Daggerfall Covenant. Were I king of the Redguard, I would have cut wages as well. nnOf course, first I would decree that these workers be bathed and the docks scrubbed clean.
Are you telling me I don't know what a Sentinel guard looks like?nnOff with you! Don't come back until you can prove what I saw was an illusion.
I can't believe my sister thinks Ohama had something to do with this! Where is Father? I demand to talk to him!

The dock master is being held in the warehouse to the northeast.nnYou'll need a key to get in. You could borrow one from a minion of the Withered Hand.nnBy "borrow," I mean "take one from his corpse after you murder him."

There's another dungeon on the west side of the ruins.nnSearch within for Altmer dead. Douse them with that censer.nnThe incense within will consecrate any bones it wafts over, preventing them from returning as undead.
Guard me while I repair the rain catcher.

When you reach the Mages Guild tower, speak to Gabrielle. She understands the need for discretion. I will meet you at the Impervious Vault. nnTu'whacca watch over you, wayfarer. Let us hope we can keep the Ansei Wards from falling into enemy hands.
The Withered Hand must pay. Kill them all!
This situation is intolerable. Deploying more guards is clearly the solution.
I should have tried to stop them. I'm sorry, so sorry. What have I done?
Glad you made it back safely, though I get the distinct feeling things didn't go well in there .
No more crime for me. I promise!nnI can change. I can change!
No one could save my father.nnAt the very least, I am glad you saved Azad.
Now that you've dealt a blow to the Withered Hand, I hope those Malooc-cursed peasants have learned their lesson.
Azah Azah is that you? What happened? I feel so dizzy
Our view didn't always clash like this. After the Akaviri War, when we were appointed, our minds were one. Lately, we've lost hold of that, and I always find myself on the opposing side.
What do I do now? Where do I go? Does the sun still shine above ground? Does the moon still come out at night?nnIt's been so long since my life was my own  I-I don't want to leave.
You must get the sabotage plans before the Withered Hand courier does. Look for a crate on the small dock to the northwest.nnHurry!
Tell Bahir to order all ships to stay in port. I must inspect them before they depart.
<This tile feels loose.>
<This tile feels loose.>
Go on now. I can't just twirl my staff and tell the Impervious Vault to open up. I need those reagents.nnHurry. I'll meet you at the vault.
I wouldn't be here, were it not for you. I pray you and the king stop the Withered Hand.
I heard that outside the valley, everyone dines like kings!
I heard that outside the valley, everyone dines like kings!
I heard that outside the valley, everyone dines like kings!
Oh, such a world! And that there should be such people in it!
Gorapples can be bought for coppers on the bushel in the Deshaan. I'll make a fortune on them.
From each font comes the poison we anoint on our blades and claws. You shall find them easily enough.nnDo not gaze too deeply into its depths, for the fumes are strongest at the source.
The Nest-Mother waits for your choice, <<1>>. We are watching.
Do not worry. I am guarding the Ward of Ansei Radan very carefully.nnI will return it to you when you are ready.
Did you help <<1>> yet?
I need help <<1>>!
Gah! Don't just stand there gawking. <<1>> is right over there. He works for the Pellingare! If he sees you, he'll kill you.
Thank you. I can't thank you enough.
You must believe me. I've done nothing wrong.nnThe investigator who arrested me is the real criminal. He's working for the Pellingare gang!
King Fahara'jad waits for you at his palace in Sentinel.nnPerhaps it would be wise to not keep him waiting long.
Have you discovered what perverts the shrine?
If you do manage to learn something from these spirits, report your findings to Telenger. You will find him in the structure near the center of the ruins.
Be welcome in our nest, friend.
Now you know what I know.nnSpeak. Will you denounce me before this crowd? Or will you hold your silence, and help me protect my people?
I suspect the messages may be hidden in the supply crates about the enclave. They cannot be so brazen as to pass them openly.
Well met, and welcome to the expedition! How do you find the ruins? Magnificent, aren't they?
Your attempts at being helpful are undeniably amusing, but I require no assistance at the moment. Now, away with you!
I understand our dear Telenger has enlisted your aid. Hmm.nnI do not know what madness grips him, but I pray your presence will soon be relieved. <<1>>.
Capture lizards for me to train, and I'll trade you valuable goods!
Why do you smell like monkeys?
This is a remarkable discovery....
It's time we were allowed to do something about these murders.

I can't believe what they're saying about Ayvas. They're faithless is all. They're part of the problem!nnWe should make them leave. All the faithless. This village is our home. If they don't want to believe in our traditional values, they can leave!
I'll deal with Ayven. His followers have abandoned him - for now that's enough. In the long term, he's going to have to fix the things he ruined.
I don't regret what I did. It was necessary.
Thank you again for everything. My daughter has learned her lesson, and our family has been reunited.nnIf we can just ride out the Fervor, then all will be well!

<<1>> should be somewhere down in these sewers. I'm going to return to the surface  it's far too dangerous here for an ordinary citizen, and my husband will take heart in knowing someone has offered to help us.
What is your choice, mortal?
Your mystery is solved.  Now join us in the revelry or get out of the way!
On your way. We have business to attend to.
I have nothing more to say to you. I am ready for the fate which awaits me.
Do not tarry long, <<1>>.  I do not know how long the others can last.  Even now I feel the <<2>>'s influence.
Oh, am I ever glad to see you again  do you have a banana? I mean  do you have a potion? To change me back?
Unishi feels sorry for the monkey, but she does what she is asked.
<<1>> must know the Shadowscales are not to blame.
Where is she? I bet that damned cat swindled me. I should have trusted my mother. Magic is no good.
Wha... what do you think you're doing? Do you not know who we are? You will pay dearly for this!
Our brother has dishonored the nest through his actions. I did not know him well, but I would not have thought him a coward.
Hopefully, <<1>> will listen to you. The longer she holds us back, the more likely another citizen will lose their life.
The bearer of the Dream Shard returns.
The old trading post is overrun by Nagas?nnHm. I suppose we won't be doing any trading there. It's a good thing Devad is so eager to help us.
Our friends in Alten Corimont need your help.
You look like you are here with some purpose, <<1>>.
Walks-in-Shade took too long in sending someone, I only hope the Archein loyalists are still there.

I am speechless. I stand bereft of words. I can think of no way to express my astonishment. A gale of awe has blown the words from my mouth. A greater man, a poet, might be able to articulate the level of amazement I feel.
<<1>> should be easy to find. The Foresters Guild is just north of here, across the bridge.

You'd think if deserters were smart, they'd leave Stormhold altogether, but not my men. No, they go to the Marshlight Inn to drink themselves into a stupor. nnI doubt they'll give you too much trouble. Just try not to rough them up too much.
<<1>> has finally got his soldiers back in order. I heard it was all thanks to you. He should have no problem with assisting you.
They took Dock Master Bahir to that warehouse in front of me.nnTo get inside, you'll need a key.nnIf you kill enough lackeys of the Withered Hand, you'll find one.
Rinlan swore he saw skeletons shambling out of the ruins in the dark of night. nnI swear. He's crazy.nnNonetheless, we need him back here. Look for him near the center of the ruins.
The Shadowscale Enclave must be made aware of these unsanctioned assassinations.
You again!
I found the seeds near the surrounding pillars of the main statue. They're little more than stone now, from time and entropy.nnI bet with a bit of polish, they could be quite a pretty decoration.
King Fahara'jad will receive you at his manse in the Royal District. It's on the south side of the city.nnMake haste! The Withered Hand grows in power each day.
If you find even one thief, you'll be helping us all.
Marimah's deep concern for the Ash'abah is the mark of a good leader.nnI wish he would care for himself as well.
Please leave me be. I must finish this antidote before  wait. Is that zehtgrass?

I don't know what we will do about the issues in our leadership.nnWe would give our lives for the caste, but we won't fall on our swords because they think we're "ideologically expendable."nnWhat can we do?
Thank you. I owe you my life.nnI will name my first child "<<1>>" in your honor.
You have been here before, yes? Old Scar-Eye knows your smell. Without the passphrase I cannot help you, strange one.
Fair tidings, <<1>>.nnTelenger will be pleased you have joined us again.
You again?nnSorry, <<1>>. There are no more executions scheduled for today.nnYou will have to find another innocent person to sentence to death.
Ah! The <<1>> returns.nnAs you can see, Telenger has hired guards for the excavation.nnYour so-called "assistance" is no longer required.

Present these reagents as an offering to Tu'whacca while I gather my strength. nnFind the door bearing Tu'whacca's image to the east. Burn the offering in the brazier that sits before it. Then I will remove the wards.
I smell death upon you. I never thought that would be a pleasing scent.nnBogmother still yearns for blood. Did you stop the Archein?
There's no need for me to ask whether the heroes had been raised when you found them.nnI only need to knoware they now at rest?
Tu'whacca's Throne is to the north.nnIf the saboteur passed that way, the Elder Throne Keeper will know.
I must remain here to guard the entrance to the deep tombs from the Withered Hand.nnMay Onsi guide your blade.
After searching these homes, I am starting to become concerned.
<<1>> has given us a great deal of renewed hope in regaining the power and respect we once held.
A goatherder's life is never easy. Lamia make it near impossible, though.
Placeholder
Justice Istah told me what you did for him. nnI am pleased he was cleared of all wrongdoing.
So far the Wardens are oblivious to our plans. They only know we seek to depose them as they did to us.
I can't wait to make an example of the Wardens once Stormhold is ours again.
I'm still working on deciphering the runes. Hopefully it won't be much longer.
Their mounds surround the Hist Tree just beyond us. By suffocating the roots, they strangle the tree.
The Blood Cult must not profit from murdering Dar'Thid's friends. Many of the good will be found near the docks in Bloodgutter. Kill any cultists and destroy any stolen goods you find.

You will not even need to remove the sword from its resting place.nnVerify its authenticity. Then activate the Soul Gem.nnOnce you are through, return here to me. We shall observe the results together.
What have you done? Without Lorkus, the Worm Cult will surely turn their backs on us.nnNo... what is this magic? Do not leave me! These servants will surely rend me apart!
The inn can be found on your right, just past the bridge.nnOr you could just follow your nose. The scent of cheap wine and liquors should choke you up when you get near enough.
Once you find a suitable artifact, do not forget to use the Soul Gem on it.
Why are you still standing here? nnI have no desire to exchange pleasantries with one such as you. nnGo find us an artifact, or be on your way.
We're in your debt. You've saved my people and our existence. I only request that you don't speak of this place. I grow concerned that others will not view our presence here as kindly as you did.
My men will see to you.
I will support Keethius as long as I believe he's doing what is right for the Cult.

I am sure you will find the one responsible for the complaints around here somewhere.nnFor now, I return to my wine until we get our marching orders. If you happen to get bored later, feel free to come back and buy me a drink.
Now that we've settled the matter with the Mirewalk Expedition, I can finally see to expanding my business!
Thanks to you, we have a sizeable well trained fighting force.  Nothing can stop us now!
Hurry up and unlock me before it's too late.
You can find J'Derr onboard the ship at the other end of Bloodgutter. Inerri is keeping Dar'Virr's raven in her private quarters.
I think Keethius will do well. He has the mindset of a leader.
Uurwen lives to the south in Gallowroot. Something must have happened to her. She wouldn't have missed our meeting otherwise.
I'm appalled by the lack of respect those mercenaries have for the dead. Granted, as mercenaries, they don't show much for the living as it is.
I don't have as much faith in Keethius as you do. But I suppose we'll see.
I can hardly believe this is real. So much has transpired.... Forgive me, dear friend, I am overwhelmed with emotion.
We should not have left her behind. Lorkhan's breath! There had to be another way....
Telenger appears quite adversely affected by today's events. Why don't you speak with him? I believe it would provide him some degree of comfort.
Uhm... that is not exactly what Ahmuzi had in mind.
Have you found my cousin? He lives to the south in Gallowroot. Something must have happened to him. He wouldn't have missed our meeting otherwise.
Thanks to you, Stillrise has finally found peace.
Have you spoken to <<1>> about the plan? I believe the hive will provide a key distraction. The Worm Cult wrote about the fleshflies as if they themselves feared them and their voracious appetite.
You have my thanks! I wouldn't have escaped without you.
Once the mine's closed, I'll send in a crew to clean out these spiders.nnThis mine used to make me gold, now all it does is cost me.
This place! Gods blood, it's horrible!
High elves in Alik'r! Imagine that!nnIf the king weren't so busy with his precious alliance, maybe he'd put a stop to this nonsense.
Travel to Bloodgutter, but do not turn your back on anyone.
Keep your weapon close to you if you are heading to the slums, yes?nnAnd if anyone tries to get near you and you don't like them, do what <<1>> does and stab them in the groin, hah!

I cannot tell you how relieved I am to hear that the Ansei Ward is safe. I will summon some of the other Ash'abah to come here and help clean out the rest of these Ra-Netu.nnYouyou must go after the third Ansei Ward.
You waste your breath. Nothing shall pass my tongue. I would cut it out before I would see it betray me so.
You were wise to support me, <<1>>. I will lead us to prosperity.
Please don't kill me! I'm not insane, I just want to get out of here!
The Hunt calls... for your blood!
Let's get out of here!
Dronoril is my name. Trapping is my business, and business has become a lot more dangerous lately.
It is best if you speak to her soon. If it comes you you have dallied within these walls unseen, there would be consequences most dire.
You are an unfamiliar one. Alten Corimont does not welcome such people. What business do you have in our town?
Three Ansei Wards protect the Alik'r. You must find the third.
<This mummy has not been raised. The other dead carried it from the deep tombs.nn<This means the deep tombs have been violated.>
You return so soon.nnHave you had any luck?
I have seen necromancers working in the sacred hall with my own eyes. If there is anything to be found, it would be there.nnBut for all our sakes, be discreet.

Whatever the Khajiit claims to be in this elixir of his is unknown to me. For all I know you could be drinking tiger's blood or guar piss.nnI would caution you against this, but it is the only lead I know of.
Hmph. Lei-Kai sticks his neck out for anyone these days. So, what'd the guards catch you doing?
You must be the agent the king sent word might be passing through. We have been awaiting your arrival.
Thanks to you, I get to see Elandra smile again.nnYour secret is safe with us. I promise, friend.
Such sweet nectar you mortals carry in your veins. A shame it goes to waste.
I hope I can start training soon.
Shiri will avenge my death and the injustices of a callous king.nnThe Withered Hand shall march over all of Alik'r, and our power shall darken the sky!
If the scouts don't get some help soon, they may be overwhelmed. Speak to one of them and offer to help defend us.
<You've found Kalas. He's dead. From the discoloration of his skin, he appears to have been poisoned.>
Be wary, we're being stalked by werewolves.

This wasn't exactly what I had in mind.nnShe's quite... furry for my taste. But you know what? This woman can drink and I admire that! nnWho knows, maybe I will try anything once? Or twice... let's not get into that.
<<1>>, your bravery and kindness have no equal. You have our thanks.
Good luck in your hunt, <<1>>. Be swift and merciless, for you would be shown no quarter were you the prey.
We're trapped! I just know we're going to get eaten.
The workers told me what you were doing. You're a good person to go out of your way for us.
It's my job to keep the beetles in check normally, but something has gotten them riled up. nnI'm a farmer, not a warrior. I don't have the weapons or skills to deal with this.
I've got a lot of steel to shape, and little enough fire to temper it.
Tell me you've done it - tell me they're not walking about anymore. I've had the most awful thoughts since you left.
Tu'whacca protect me!

First things first. We need some meat from the nearby mudcrabs. Can't very well have <<1>> without the mudcrab, can you?nnYou'll find them on the beach west of us. I'll speak to some of the traders and see about getting the necessary supplies.

We must be more precise with our measurements.nnA little too much of this, a little not enough of that, and kabloom! The whole thing's ruined.nnI have faith in you. The mudcrabs have faith in you. You can do it.
I can't thank you enough for your help. If you hadn't come along, they'd still be trapped or worse eaten for dinner.
I'm not going to hang around here much longer. I'll find a nice, quiet job in Sentinel. Maybe get work on the docks!
<<1>> is at the southern end of the camp. You should speak with him there, if you intend to challenge him for leadership of the Cult.
Is that the ore from the Kulati Mines? I sure hope so!
Mercy, please, no more!nnI did everything your master bid me, and told no one of our dealings. I swear it... by my father's grave, I swear it! I would never cross Death's Consort.
What news do you have for me?
Be wary, <<1>>. The lingering Imperials and their atronach servants will be a danger you must overcome.
I take it you do not have good news for me, by the looks of it.
I see from your face that it is as I feared. The Hist has been harmed. Have the pirates paid for their desecration of the Hist?
Best to forget we ever talked. Benefits the both of us.
Speak to me no more. As with the other, the one you slew beneath our very feet, I will be named no longer.nnBitterness shall be my drink, and remorse my fruit. Leave me be.
I see great things ahead for you, <<1>>.nnSeek out <<2>> in the building below the tower to learn the philosphy of our blademasters.
Haha, this one thinks the elf is afraid of a little fur.nnPerhaps I can show him that it can keep him quite warm, yes?
And for our twelth child, we should name him after my second brother's thirteenth child's fourth kid, who I thought was just adorable! What was her name again....
I sensed you moving about the ruins of this place, communing with the dead. Have my fellows found someone who can help us restore the land?
It pains us all to have to destroy our Lost brothers and sisters, but don't fret, <<1>>. Have you killed many?
It will take time to restore order to Leki's Blade. Remnants of our old masters must be put aside forever.nnJustice was served, and its taste is bitter to me.
You have learned all we have to offer. May it protect you in your travels.
You have learned to defend yourself from multiple angles of attack.nnMay this knowledge serve you well in your travels.
Even if you never pick up a shield, you must learn how it can be used against you.
May you strike down all opponents in your path.
Did you hear those roaring fires outside? I'm afraid it set all my things on edge! Especially the wooden ones. The poor things are trembling with fear.
I am glad you wish to be a part of the hatching. You honor us.
Do you smell something burning?nnI thought I smelled something burning.
Tei-Shak is young. Clever, but incautious.nnFire is an uncertain ally. Like a slaughterfish, it bites whatever is nearby. You are lucky it didn't devour you.
I heard the news. Thank you, <<1>>.nnMaybe the madness will ebb as time passes. Maybe there's no exit. At least it can't get worse.
Your potential is obvious. I can see you've handled challenges before. Welcome to our school, recruit.nnAre you here to prove yourself, as have so many others before you?
Show no mercy. Find my husband and kill him and any werewolf you find. If we don't stop them, they'll kill everyone in Gallowroot!
You are too late. It is already done.
I've seen some of the members you've trained. They seem to walk just a little bit taller than everyone else.

The eastern areas of the Mire are dangerous. The witchlights dazzle the Bogwild, then whisper the lies that make their brains fold into bad shapes.nnBe careful. Don't believe the witchlights' stories.

Thank Onsi! I don't have much time, stranger. Hearken to my words of warning.nnWe were attacked by a Withered Hand army led by the necromancer <<1>>. The army has withdrawn, but the necromancer isn't done with Tava's Blessing yet.
I have heard what you've done to prepare for our hatching, <<1>>. The eggs move, and the hatching will happen soon.
Go back to your friend. I'm sure he's lying on those nice sunny rocks.nnHeh.
I suppose only time will tell how Mirewalk will fair. Since your exposure was so slight, I'd assume the affects of the gas will wear off soon.
Remember, the rock must be thrown first, otherwise it won't mix with the gas to make it flammable.
I'm not sure you can trust what this boar has to say. In fact, I'm not sure you can trust a talking boar at all.
The farms are more stable now. Orc blood will feed the fish, and food will make its way to the hungry.nnI relish this opportunity to do good, real work. This forest is a blessing, dangers or no.
What language was the spy speaking in? I couldn't understand a word of it!

The pirates are to the east of us. You should look for someone on the outskirts.nnIf you go too far into their camp, they'll attack. Maybe they're trying to hide something. Maybe they're just violent psychopaths driven by greed.nnWho am I to say?
I hope Lucan accepted my offer. I'll be seeing him shortly.
Have you made your decision?

Maybe I'm wrong. I don't know. My claws are dull, but the winds from my mind have still blown strong until now.nnGo now. Murder pirates for those who died here. And if you can find out why they're here, meet me on the far side of their camp.

I did not think I would find a burglar so easily! Oh, apologies... I'm sure you are much more than a common thief, by the looks of you.nnThe merchants probably keep their manifests within their homes. Much more secure than the docks, I would think.
If you think you can survive your proving, only Master Fadalia can tell you more.

I wouldn't normally ask a stranger to help, but you look like you can handle yourself better than most. And, if you do manage to find something, <<1>> won't hesitate to reward you for your help. He's hiding on the island at the bottom of the basin.
If you've come for a shipment, you'll be waiting a while.
I pray nothing has happened at the mines.nnWithout raw ore, we cannot continue to produce weapons for the king's army.
I suppose Kee-Scale never did admit to being a thief. His slaver insisted he'd been captured within a Thieves' Guild nest. Perhaps he was simply... lost.
You must hurry. The message is of great importance. The Hissmir need to understand the dangers everyone will face should they lose the Gilded Skull.
Trouble someone else with your stories.
I will head to the grove shortly.
What, do you want me to give you directions on how to kill things? Get to it!
My heart is heavy with worry for the town of Satakalaam. May your journey be safe, friend!
You can't miss them, <<1>>. Well, I suppose you could, if I were masking them.
Be careful on your travels, friend. Hopefully, <<1>> doesn't prove to be too dangerous.nnIf that's truly where <<2>> has moved the wards, you may need to face him.
Keethius is a tyrant. I'm leaving at the first sign of trouble.
Keethius is a snake. I don't know if I can follow his rule.
It is a terrible thing to destroy the sap of a Hist. But it would be worse to let Imperials and cultists have it.nnThey are unworthy of its blessings.
Have you done your good deed for the day, footpad?
I can already feel myself fading. I am free of this anchoring sorrow, and I have you to thank, <<1>>.
Do as I told you, and quickly - I can't make a move until I've got some distraction.  Go!
Any luck finding out about the Maormer fleet, or my scout?
Have you made any progress?
What are you waiting for? Destroy those vile things!
Most of my family is gone, <<1>>. I hope you find whatever is responsible for this, and bring it to a painful end!
The supplies and the chest are both found in the pirate camp to the east of here. Look along the shore, where they're loading those small boats.

You would attempt to stop the coming storm? To stand in the dragon's breath armed with nothing but hope?nnEither a fool or hero stands before me. I have yet to decide which.nnNo matter. Prove yourself worthy, and my knowledge shall be yours.
Thank you... if anything for revealing the truth that is right in front of my eyes.nnThat is... if these are actually eyes I'm seeing through.
The gas is gone, but I can still hear breathing coming from the walls. <<1>> believes it will fade away, but I don't want it to! I couldn't bear never learning who was trapped within the walls.
Did you see those fires? I thought I was imagining them, but <<1>> said she could see them too. nnLooks like they burned that gas completely away. I wonder what this will mean for Mirewalk.
It's too bad those fires didn't catch on to this tree. Then those little deviants would be forced to come down and face me!
I hope with the gas gone, it will put an end to all the unwelcome guests.
I am sorry, but the task before you must be done on your own.nnPerhaps in time, you will learn our virtues as if they were your own. Now go. The spirits of my comrades must be freed once and for all.
I feel terrible.nnI'm still in the middle of a pirate camp, aren't I?
May you know the joy you brought to my family and I.nnMay any dangers on your path tremble at your approach!
Thank you for delivering this letter. Although the truth is hard to accept, it's good to know his fate is no longer a mystery.nnMy wife will be devastated. He was always her favorite.
I thank you friend, you have made me a happy man. If there is a wedding, you will be invited.
Shamar and I will see each other soon. I am sure we will have quite an adventure together.
You may be worthwhile afterall.  I will reconsider my opinion of you. If you excel you may one day become my equal.
We heard the runner had headed northeast to Silvenar to make the delivery. Thank you for your help!
Spiders are bad enough. Giant spiders - that's enough to make a brave man cry like a babe. Or wet his breeches.
We heard the runner had headed northeast to Silvenar to make the delivery. Thank you for your help!
Just give me a moment to finish my elixir.
<<1>> doesn't remember what it was like to be free. Thank you, walker. We will not forget your help.
I'll stay here to make sure the farmers get out safely. You've been a great help here!
If the Withered Hand ever does try to take Bergama, we will now fight twice as hard to defend it. nnThis city will persevere. And you will always be welcome here.
To harm the dreameater asp is an unforgivable sin. Their venom is easily milked from their fangs with a quick hand and a keen eye.nnYou will find them here, hiding among the brambles and houses.
Do not fear the venom, <<1>>. It is from fear we strike out and seek to do harm. The serpent within us does not seek to harm.nnOnce you have done so, the elder will be free.
No! No, you weren't supposed to find me!
Bring me any harpy eggs you find.nnThen you can help me figure out what to do with them.
I hear there are pirates to the east. How quaint.nnThey do know the sea is far to the north of here, yes?
Have you claimed the life of the creature?
The other day, I saw a Dunmer with a missing leg lying on the rocks here.nnI don't think he quite understood the Strand.
My sister told me that you assisted Arch-Mage Telenger and fought a necromancer!nnI do not suppose you are also a reknowned magus seeking apprentices?
What is that you have there?
I'm not sure where Gatheon's children are, but perhaps in the place of many dwellings what is it called? nnElden Root.
I think there's a pebble on my rock.
Telenger does amazing, valuable work, but it can be dangerous. I heard one of his apprentices vanished on an expedition to Alik'r once.
Better not speak too loudly of distaste for the Crowns, friend, or you may be the next to disappear.
One thing is certain. I'm not walking the streets alone any time soon.
I'm not afraid of going out at night, but neither am I a fool.nnUntil this mystery is solved, I'm staying near my friends.

You're still young. Back in Helstrom, I'm old enough to be considered the local wise-man.nnI haven't decided if I like that. I don't feel wise. Unless "wise" is just a nice way of saying I tell dull stories about the way things used to be.
Did you find Riane? Was she hurt?
The dead boar is wearing a decorative collar. Faded symbols adorn the fur. Its throat is slit, and patches of dried blood can still be seen on the surrounding ground.
Come closer and I'll bleed you like I did your friends. I am slave to no one, mer or lizard!
You have the musk. Yes? Yet you delay. Hmm?
By my honor your bravery is great, friend! Thank you for what you did for the Lion Guard soldiers. May Tu'whacca watch over you, all of your days.
This food is enough for me, thank you.
I'm still weak, but the chill is gone. nnYou've done it. You've saved my soul!
The deeply hidden embers glow brightly as they're freed from their coating of ash and re-exposed to the air. They quickly bring flames back to the remaining wood.

Rumor has it you've taken up with Idrasin the trader. He's a crook. He treated the poor beggars of Alakad badly, taking advantage of our condition to pay us next to nothing for or work. Abandon your deal with him. Work for us!
Don't speak to me! I know you sold my treasure to the beggars! Get out of my sight before I give you the thrashing you deserve, you honorless cur!
The sooner you find those poor young things, the better. They may be suffering.nnPlease be quick.
<This door is locked.>
Have you made them pay for what they did? I would help you, but... it is so dangerous there... what a weak man I am!
Even with the Cult gone, I'd still like to see the Archeins and Wardens destroy eachother!

<The last entry reads:>nn"My mother fell ill today. I'm terrified, but she thinks she found a ritual to protect the rest of us.nn"Those of us who are healthy have been told to go to the shrine and pray."

I hope you are satisfied with yourself. You are lucky I have a cooler head than Elennae - she would have incinerated you, whereas I am above such things.nnI will merely await my next opportunity to impress!
I'd rather die than return to Lainlyn! Thank you for your concern, but I've found happiness here.nnBe careful on your return. Harpies expect aggression from strangers, so they often strike first.
My gratitude for your deeds will last as long in my heart as my hatred for the Withered Hand and those vile ogres!
Defeat the guardians to shatter the spell.nnDo not worry about me. The time for my passing has been too long in coming.nnThe Tear must be yours.
Out of work, out of water  what a sorry state we're in!
The desert is not meant for the living. Our Yokudan ancestors made a mistake settling here. Now we are paying the price.
This villager clings to a small totem in one hand and a stone tablet in the other. The tablet appears to be an ancient pictogram, the etchings well-worn with age.
Tell me, what news have you of Zakavit and Fermouzh?
We were actually getting ahead for a change, storing extra barrels of water for Sentinel.nnEven after we clear the beetles out, we'll be struggling to catch up.
Go on, do what you have to do. Before I fall down.
Go, take care of the sap. Don't worry about me.

The Lion Guard is in your debt, <<1>>. I wish you well in your travels!nnAs soon as Destane recovers we will be on our way. I think we will travel to Sep's Spine to investigate the rumors of a Withered Hand Army in that direction.
Three tokens. That's all you need!nnThree tokens and this wonderful prize voucher is all yours! Doesn't that sound wonderful?nnThink of the marvelous things you could use it on!
No doubt Istah is spreading poison and lies about me. May Stendarr have mercy on his soul. The justices certainly will not.nnTruly, Istah should never have been issued his blades.
<<1>>! You must know I did not murder Inila or Fakimal.nnYou can try speaking to <<2>> on my behalf, but I suspect your pleas will fall on deaf ears.
You have the look of one who has goods to trade. Am I wrong?
Have you learned anything new?
First I was supposed to keep people from entering the Worm Cult camp. Now I'm supposed to keep them from leaving it.nnIt's a funny old world.

I was concerned that I may not be able to complete my research here, and nearly thought this a lost cause.nnThanks to you, this will turn out to be productive despite our setbacks thus far.nnHave you ever considered an apprenticeship?
<<1>> must be stopped!nnThe people of <<2>> had no concept of the evil she represented.

I have to admit, <<1>>, I am somewhat jealous. While I have spent years working to impress Telenger, you have managed to do so as if it were the work of an afternoon.nnI am inspired. I shall be working to emulate your strengths.
Why are you here? I think we've concluded our business.
So many people have come here to collect water, you shouldn't have trouble finding water urns.nnGet the healing waters to my troops. They'll be on their feet in no time.

The people of Hissmir will never know how close we came to spilling their blood. With patience and hard work, we might give them benefits of Tamrielic culture.nnThe Archeins can make their lives better. I'm sure of it.
Thank you for saving me. Venosir is too wounded to travel on his own.
I've heard you saved us. Thank you.nnI didn't fear death, but Naja gave his life for me. I must try to go on.
I sense a change in the air. Is it finished?
Go! Waste no time in visiting Sep's wrath on the lamia!
I'll leave in a moment  just getting my courage up
I hope <<1>> took the message seriously. He is running out of time.
Good. You made it. Prepare yourself now. If we falter here, the Alik'r will fall into Shikri's clutches.
Have you learned anything?

Go on now. Don't be shy.nnI'm rather untalented in the games they play, but that voucher they offer can be quite valuable.nnYou earn enough tokens and give them to the Master, you win a voucher. That voucher ends up with me, you get your information.

<<1>> said the gas was burned out by a fire. I assume that means your little visits will be over soon.nnWhere are the little ones? I thought I just heard them.nnStrange.nnWell, I'm sure they're just playing outside somewhere.
<<1>>, you live. I relish the fact that I will not have to carry your corpse away from these fiends.nnThe Night Mother spoke to me moments before you arrived. There may yet be hope for our brothers.
Have no pity for oathbreakers.nnThe Worm Cult was told they could do what they wished with the souls and corpses of other races. Saxhleel souls have a different obligation.

We've cut off the head. Now our forces gather to dismember the body. They don't even know they're dead yet.nnAnd then - then we'll deal with the pirates who violate our Hist. We won't be kind to them.

First, you will face the Nedic Peoples. When the Ra Gada first crashed on these shores, the Nedes were first to challenge them.nnFight the Nedic soldiers' spirits. Claim their essences, and use them to summon and face their leader, Warchief Haakon.
If you find the harpy eggs, take them to Daneem right away.nnHe's over by <<1>> now.
I'm keepin' watch for any stragglers. I truly can't thank you enough my friend.
Oh, you lose. Even with the cheese!nnHow do you lose with cheese? Really?
Did you find him? Is my Captain alive?
Oh, ho, you're a clever one, aren't you! I guess you found my note and decided to look over here, didn't you! You're smarter than these pirates, I bet they never gave the note I left a second look.
I could hear the fighting from here. If attacking dreugh can't keep Captain Ravenil's men occupied for a while, I don't know what will.
Thank you so much. I'm going to catch my breath, then make a run for the entrance. nnIf you can find my brother, I'll meet you both at the front of the caves.
I heard you are the one responsible for returning our memories. Why would you do that? We all came here willingly. We wanted to forget!
This one must die! Slay her, and add her blood to Sithis' reign! Be bathed in your master's glory through her sacrifice!
That did not go as planned. What happened?
Fine weather we're having, isn't it? Hot and humid with a chance of spriggans.
I must petition my superiors for reassignment. This place is a bit too exciting, eh?
What did he say?
My life swiftly flees, but I would not want a kindred survivor to suffer my fate. The necromancers must not continue to entrap my brothers.nnTheir hubris must be repaid in kind.
Without your help, <<1>>, I doubt that I would have ever been freed. A mere thanks doesn't seem sufficient for all that you have done.
Since you killed the Sin Eater, I'm starting to remember things about myself that I regret. In the past, I was not the sort who would have defended the law.

It's easy you see. Drink from this little mixture I've put together. Once the effects have taken place, you must find the only entrance that only you will be able to enter.nnYou make it there, you save your friend.nnOh, and be mindful of the cats.
Though some anoint themselves with the blood, I have seen others carry a vial with them. Find one and discover the true purpose of this necromancy.
I'm keepin' watch for any stragglers. I truly can't thank you enough my friend.
There you are! I could barely believe my eyes, when I saw Hram running out of those snake-ridden caves.
Nice work! I could hear the commotion from here. Ever since Captain Ravenil's men arrived, I've thought my opportunity to find the treasure was lost.
Thank you, friend.nnThank you for taking the risk in helping me in all of this. Be sure to let my guard know at Silvenar... let them know what happened this day.
