Anamara says we're leaving soon. Not soon enough, to my mind! I owe you my life, <<1>>.
I'm going to let my captain know what happened. At least we now know why the dreugh moved northward.

Thank you for helping me. I know not all of the villagers will be happy to have their memories back, but forgetting my husband was far too high a price.nnAbandoning our past was never the right answer. We must face it and learn from it.
<This appears to be the tent the Dominion Soilder spoke of. If you had a fire source of some kind, you would be able to burn it.>
It looks like Harus wants to talk to you. I'll do you the favor of not asking what about.
Have you found any rings? I was given the one I gave you by a man in town, to be honest. His wife had run with the Gray Sails and he wanted no more to do with her - or them.
<The warhorse looks far more relaxed now that it is back near Haleh.>
If you wish to speak with Thahala, call her with that horn.
Do not worry. Ma'Zarman will meet you at the entrance of the bazaar, he promises.
The Hist-Licker returns! Have the eggs been moistened by your hands?
Ohhh, look at the cute rat!nnMa'Zarman could eat you, you are so cute!
Please, speak to Akr-Bihada. The dead will overwhelm us soon!
What is all that commotion out there? It is disturbing my drink here.
I hear that you are being honored by the elder. nnYou represent all Nords in this. Be sure to treat their honor with respect.
They're honoring YOU? I've been studying them for years. Apparently they respect brute force more than careful study.
My king should not be so quick to dismiss the old tales.nnThese missing weapons bode ill for all of Alik'r.

You did not have the right to interfere with our affairs. People came here to forget. They did this willingly. nnYou have forced them to face a past they had tried to leave behind. You should leave this place. Now.
If news leaked out that the Ansei Wards were missing, panic would result in Sentinel.nnOur people rightly fear necromancy, and this is an ill omen indeed.
Thank you for helping us bury these poor souls. It would be a crime to leave them untended, rotting under the desert sun or eaten by scavengers.
What brings you to me today, child?
You drink well! Even for a <<1>>.nnYou have gained my respect this day. Please, feel free to challenge me again, anytime.
I'm impressed.nnI did not expect one such as yourself to drink so well.
Hurry to Bergama. The Withered Hand may be there already.
Though I am glad you understand, I'm sure we can both agree that this business is still dreadful.nnUnfortunately, Istah will simply have to remain in the stocks for the time being.
That monstrous creature must have done something to <<1>>!
Please do not disturb the eggs.
You should question the guards in Bergama.nnFind out if any of them know the current location of <<1>>.

I have informed your friends of what has happened and they have already moved on in their travels. I made sure no harm came to them.nnThis cave is open for your use. I do advise that you stay away from the bazaar. Valaydia's minions still roam about.
You have Keeba-sho's thanks for making sure no one steals profit from his hard work.
The people at the Sunscale Strand must know how dangerous these pirates are.
I'll keep a much better eye on him now. Thank you again, <<1>>.
They still have no idea we're here.nnThey'll know when we attack, I suppose.

You know our plans, yes? You were the one who sent Relazar to feed the trees.nnWe move slowly but steadily against the rest of them. But we must be cautious. Some of us have eaten the food of the Cult. Those ones smell different now.
Is it me, or are there are lot more people whispering around the camp lately? I can't understand it.nnI'd love to have another bowl of that whatever-it-is the Cult has been making us for dinner.
The Prophet was adamant that you should bring "The Broken Staff" to him. But if the thief finds passage on a ship out of Koeglin, we may never see that book again.
Still alive eh? You're faster than you look.
The wraiths surrounded this place once you left. What do they want, <<1>>? Make them leave us be!
You have obtained the Varla Key. Once again, mortal, you have exceeded my grandest expectations.nnAre you prepared for what lies beyond?
Zud-Reen still breathes? His will is truly a thing to behold.nnMay the Hist watch his steps in that treacherous place.

Oh no, oh no! How did this happen?nnThe Thane is going to kill me. He's really going to do it this time! He was kidding all the other times but this time he's really going to do it!nnOh, uh, I didn't see you there! Everything is fine! Haha!
You must be the one Leonce mentioned. nnI understand you've been helping our negligent novice?
Bring me that goblin's head!
Yes, yes, read the note. It's still right over there in front of the door.
I've no use for hired hands who fail at their job. Good day.
<The Ayleid tablet is covered in moss and prying vines, but you can make out the embossed script through the grime.>
I hope you understand that I was trying to help the inmates of Black Rose Prison. Killing the Sin Eater destroyed years of work. I only hope these people don't go back to their criminal ways.
Keep heading back to the north-east. You'll find our Treethane in the central most home.nnHe'll want to hear about how easily you stumbled upon this town.
You'll find <<1>>'s home to the north.nnSpeak to him and find out what you can. We must get the focus in place to renew the spell, otherwise our shields will fall and all will be lost.

Use the wand on the chickens.nnIf they happen to have the crystals, you should be able to extract them. If they don't... well, I'm not really sure.nnAs a matter of fact, don't tell me what happens. It's better that way.
We heard some fighting going on. Everything all right?
Yendirwen is very firm about enforcing Bosmer traditions. This most recent issue with the Green Pact is just another one of her crusades.
Are all of the urns in place?
<<1>> will loose a lot of business if he doesn't return soon.
Leave me alone!
Don't hurt me!
Thank you for saving me!
Ever since I started fishing with this Dunmer pole-thing, I've wanted to drink an intoxicating beverage.
It is here: The <<1>>. I can feel it!nnWhat was lost is now found. And yet a strangeness surrounds this thing. Place it in my hands. I will see its strength at last.

We must move quickly to free the prisoners before they are taken to the alters to be killed and brought back to life as Risen.nnAny Risen who are faithful to The Huntress will have a key you can use to open the cell doors and free the prisoners.

Search the area and see if you can find anything that'll tell us what Mahnor has revealed.nnWe have to be quick. If we don't find out what's been leaked soon, the Imperials will be on Vulkwasten before we know it.
You have what you came here for.nnIt's too late though. You'll never get to them in time.

The only way to destroy the altars is to use fire. Scorching their surface will burn away the runes that give the altars the power to raise the dead and make it impossible to recreate the runes.nnBathe them in fire and deny The Huntress her slaves.

It was supposed to be a routine mission. Go to the Imperial camp to the north-west and make sure their army wasn't any closer to finding us.nnBut the crystals weren't delivered and she's still gone. Something must have gone wrong. Please find her.
It's unbelieavable to me how long I was fooled by The Huntress.nnAs soon as the altars are on fire return and speak with me again. I want to know when the deed is done.
I know the Risen below will fight you to the death but I'm sure in their hearts they secretly long for this all to be over.
Now no one can harm the forest in the same way as these intruders have. I will let others clean up these broken fools, now.nnThank you, <<1>>, you have proven a worthy ally.
By the greens of the forest, what was that creature that attacked you?nnI had heard tales of someone throwing a small pet into a pond years ago, but... well I didn't think there was any truth to it!
Now that you've put the sleep potion in the kegs, we can bargain for Miranda's release. nnBut let's find out where she is. Search the counting house for clues to where they're keeping her.
Search the houses for jewels, and collect puffball caps from the dock. Then meet me near the boathouse.nnYou could steal clothes from a dead bandit and disguise yourself .

We felt the surge of magic as the tome was destroyed. I... admit I am disappointed, <<1>>. Denying it to our enemies is at least some consolation, but lacking that tool will slow our assault down significantly.
We have to go in there, don't we? Will you go ahead first, as you have before?nnI need a moment to... gather my strength. And wits.
We are sorry for taking your totem. We are returning it to your campnnWait a minute  is that you? You certainly look  different.
How do you know about the Worm Cult?nnThose outside our order shouldn't be privy to such information.nnWho sent you here?
So you know now.nnThorne and Layliana cannot be together. Why my poor brother cannot see that this wasn't meant to be is beyond me.nnLove blinds him. I feel for him. I really do.
Your name will always be honored at Cumberland's Watch.
Good luck in your task, <<1>>.
With your help perhaps we can turn the tide against The Huntress and end the threat she poses, once and for all.
Safia sent you? nnLet me guess. She's worried.
Our focus must remain on the Huntress and her actions.nnI cannot worry about Thorne. Not now. nnIf only things could have turned out differently....
Layliana looks so sad lately.nnI really wish there was something I could do to cheer her up. Maybe a song and dance? My brother and I used to know a fair number about the forests.
Have you brought something?
At last! The <<1>>! nnThe old man has been raving about that thing for a mammoth's age.
I should not have left my egg-brother in Mirewalk. We should have travelled the fens together.
<The embers are smouldering, yet they are cold to the touch. As you reach your hands toward the brazier, you hear a strange voice in your head, speaking in some foreign tongue.>
The pain of loss has eased now that <<1>> is here.
What is this that you bring me?
Hand of Auri-El, I have never been so glad to see a <<1>>.
Please, hurry. The shrine is in Ildroth. Maybe once the offering is made, the Shadowscale will not want to kill me.
I think Serge poisoned me. I feel nauseous and weak.nnHe taunted me by saying there's a crate of something that would act as an antidote along the east beach. Please hurry!
Oh no! My lady! She's  dead? I should've tried to help her myself!nnYou know what this means? Now I have to find a new job!
Look at my little kitten. Isn't he a dear thing? You know, he charms everyone. Since Caspian has come along, my sales have doubled.
The Skull of Yotunmir... how could I have forgotten? Mannimarco and his Worm Cult must not be allowed to find it.
So Muzgu and the Daedra are dead. nnNow what? Can we be done with the killing?
By the First Forge, look at thisa new recruit! You are planning on joining up aren't you?nnWait, I'm getting ahead of myself. Welcome to the Wayrest Fighters Guild Hall!
You did it! nnThe dreugh are pulling back. Bless you.
My leg! One of these ruffians broke my leg!
Stendarr save us! Did I hear fighting upstairs?
Here and there through these ruins, you'll find the bare dirt where once trees flourished. Plant my seeds there.

Lokk's Orcs pride themselves on their battle prowess? They'd do much better if they'd show up.nnI wouldn't want to suggest anything out of sorts, but if one of them had a knife in their belly, I wouldn't be disappointed.
I have enough relics to ship out today. If you want to dig through Imperial garbage again, there's always tomorrow.
How can I help you, sister?

Ah, listen to this. I'm working on a new ballad - here's the end bit.nnThe Dreamer has awakened,nHis former wrath abhorrednWith Reason's gracenDishonor chasednAnd Hosni's house restored.nnIt's about you, you know.
<<1>> is a good man. Do not judge his madness too harshly. Every person in our tribe succumbed to the disease while he was left untouched. It is enough to drive anyone insane.
I was joking about you picking your teeth with dragon bones. Now I'm not so sure you don't.
You should probably concentrate on the fight.
You're a better fighter than you look.
I'd go with you if I could, <<1>>, but I can't leave him alone, not here.nnCrack some skulls for me, eh?
One day, this will be passed, like any other smelly obstruction.nn...though I still think <<1>> and <<2>> should stop playing in the filth.
Go ahead. If you have the guts to take it, it's yours.

Finally, someone around here who gets things done!nnThe Supernal Dreamers are prowling along the shore southwest of the estate. The guard at the back gate will let you out.nnI'll look forward to hearing the carnage. Make it loud!
Everything is ready, but I must be certain. When I expel this Daedra, it will be drawn into the cultistand he will die.nnAre you sure you're willing to sacrifice this man?
I hear you've been busy.nnIf you've earned a favor from S'Rashi, you should put it to good use. I think he might know stole the Dream Shard.
Hold your nose. The stench just gets worse. Goblins, ogres  there's an army of them down there.nnI don't care if King Emeric himself orders itthe Lion Guard advances no further.
Mannimarco must not be allowed to find the Skull of Yotunmir.
The wraiths surrounded this place once you left. What do they want, <<1>>? Make them leave us be!

Rajeren sees what you have done here, and the sun shines once again at this temple.nnShe still remains, but you have proven your ability to face her and weather her storms. You will need to face her, before the sun will shine brightly all over.

No matter what we did, we couldn't hurt her. The Huntress used her own magic to give us life once before. Clearly she would not allow her own creations be used against her.nnIt's hopeless. Continuing this fight only guarantees our death once again.
<<1>>! You're the one responsible for all this?nnI wish I had a hundred more like you back when I went against the Imperials the first time.
We get downpours like that one every once in a while. It's a swamp. You come to expect it.
If I don't untangle these lines soon, I will try catching crabs with my bare hands.

Layliana and I are going to make a break for the ruins to the west. Keep them occupied long enough for us to call the others.nnPlease, <<1>>, I know this is asking a lot, but... I don't know what else to do.
Eboth-mok is busy. You go pester someone else, yes?
Thanks for your help with that gang of thugs.nnOn to the next mission! I've got to see to this guard's needs. Good day!
What can I do for you?
You should follow <<1>>. He may need... someone.nnLoriasel lies to the west of here. It's a large complex of Ayleid ruins - you will know it when you see it.

The skull may have left Hissmir, but who's to say the Worm Cult will believe that. My coterie will continue to stockpile arrow- and spear-heads. It is preferable to have them and not need them than it is to need them and not have them.
Good luck and be careful. Remember, meet me outside of the east entrance once you've obtained the Dream Shard. I'll be waiting by the stables.
<<1>> has left to return the skull to the Ayeleids? I doubt they'll thank us. Even in death, they're arrogant.nnI respect their power and knowledge, but their demeanor draws flies.
Say, I heard you recently arrived from Alcaire.nnThere are terrible rumors about Duchess Lakana. Are they true? Was she murdered?
She's coming out of it. I saw her eyes flicker. Azura be praised.
High King Emeric is eager to speak with you. nnOne does not keep His Majesty waiting.
Go. Tell <<1>> I am leaving.
Since <<1>>  left for Loriasel, it feels as if a weight has been taken off our village.

If you develop your mind, you may one day possess the wisdom of a weaver.nnMatching the nimbleness and accuracy of our claws is another matter. If you wish, perhaps we will teach you in the future, egg-sibling.
May the Eight bless you. And yes, I'm an Orc and a priest. Orcs can be priests. Though I admit, it's probably not that common a sight.
Do you know the names of everyone you've killed?
A village is like unto water.nnIf you try to calm it with the work of your hands, you will only disturb it more. Stay your hands, and it will become tranquil on its own.

You travel the world, never resting. You have adventures worthy of being told around the fire, when it is down to embers, and the sky is blue in the east.nnIt seems like a sad life to me. I would rather sleep in my own hut and tend my reed-patties.
This one is very grateful that you will be helping his brother.nnS'rashi is a good and honest worker for the Midnight Union. He's only fallen on hard times. This one is glad you understand.

Perhaps we can now have a civil conversation. I'm Perry. Brother Perry, traveling through Alcaire on my way back to Pariah Abbey.nnIngride Vanne offered me a room for the night. It just happened to be the night the Supernal Dreamers attacked.
Shh! Not right now. Just leave me here for a few more minutes.

Old <<1>> is returning to Loriasel. I can't believe he went alone. Didn't anyone tell him about the threat of the Worm Culrt?nnWe should have given him an escort of hunters, armed with our sharpest weapons.
Welcome to Hissmir.nnYou have goods from outside the village? I have many eager buyers. It doesn't matter what you have. They buy everything. Very foolish of them. But good for you, yes?
There is a pressure in the air. Like a storm is coming. But there is only you.nnCurious.
Our customs of hospitality say I must greet you. But my liver flops. It says you are an ill guest.nnWhy is that?
What more is there to say between us?
The one called Rajeren has proven more than we can handle, but perhaps you can kill him and aid us in victory!
Compared to the rest of these people, you're a really generous person. Of course  that's not saying much.
Hosni taking the Dream Shard might explain the presence of those vipers, the Supernal Dreamers. nnThat only increases anxiety about Sirali  and my suspicions about Adima.
Farewell, Unbeliever. The guardians of Maruhk will soon show you the path you have chosen - that of your own destruction.

You must muster everthing you can to destroy her.nnThe Risen will be of no help on this one, I'm afraid. We all believe in you. This is for all of Valenwood. nnIf you are succesful, I will be gone, but you have my thanks in advance.
There must be some way to get through to Hosni.
My Hosni dreams. nnIf you go inside, do not disturb him. It would make me angry.
This should be the last load of scrap I have to send gro-Izburg .nnNow tell him that we are even.
Triumphant, I hope? You certainly have been gone long enough. nnWait a minute. Where's the sword?
The river that the Blackmaul set upon us provides a means for their undoing.
Now I must find ways to make amends. nnI know one thingthe days of the Midnight Union are over.
What's happened? There was a terrible commotion in the manor house. nnI think I might try to leave now.
I heard Count Hosni's gone upstairs to his chambers again. nnI've never seen a man sleep as much as he does.
What in Oblivion is going on in the manor? nnI'd go see myself, but, wellI'm frightened.
Head to the cave at the top of Shinji's Scarp. Meanan told me that the stone column is at the bottom of the cave next to a blocked stairwell. One good hit with the pickaxe should shatter the column.
Go now. Destroy the aberration. It must be done.
Is the captain dead? Is <<1>> safe?nnThe thought of becoming a rug for the captain's cabin has left <<1>> unable to eat or sleep.

There is death in the captain's eye, death for <<1>>! Little does he know that you're on your way to kill him.nnHe's measuring his cabin to see where Dro'farahm's skin will look best. The ship is to the south. Save <<1>>, please!
Oh yes, I can sense that you want to be the hero. But to rescue the countess, you will have to come through into my world!nnPlease. Do come in!
Lead on. I'll follow.
I feel so empty. Like there's no one here. I am not a person. I'm just a reflection.

Trying to repair the totem? That is generous of you. Of course, if the trade coteries were doing what they should, we couldn't need generous stranger to do it for us.nnWe'll never resist the necromancers in this state.
You waiting for a tip? nnGet a move on and return to Outfitter Wickton, or I will start demonstrating mace attacks on you.
Fell's Run is north of here, past the tor.nnMore Orcs have settled in that town, so watch your tongue  and keep your weapons ready.
Have you talked to the quartermaster yet?
Truly, we thought the crown lost to the ages. Karine was sent on a fool's errand, yet here the crown sits before me!
Please, have mercy!
Poor Michel. Breloth left him with two kids. He'll have to find someone else soon.nnAfter all, three in the family is never good.

Breloth was such a dear friend, but much like my eggs, she was fragile. Michel turned his back one moment, and then she was dead  broken .nnThat's why these eggs require constant supervision and care.
It was nice doing business with you.

Why did you make him leave? I was this close to reaching the peace of death!nnIt has just been a jestthe Daggerfall Covenant, my kingdom, my life. I was never worthy to be king. I'll die here and one more worthy will take my place.
Am I cursed? My home was attacked. This camp was attacked. I don't know where to go or what to do any more.
I will never forget the sacrfice my wife and so many others made for us in Crestshade.
Be sure you take that report directy to <<1>> and no one else.
Are you really taking instruction from Ashton?nnLook, I don't want to speak ill of a Grandmaster but  if she starts waving a soul gem at you, run. Run, and don't look back.
Thank you so much for what you've done!nnIf it wasn't for you, I would be dead. My father would still be under the Supernal Dreamers' spell!
The Covenant thanks you for joining the war effort! With talented crafters like yourself at our back, there's no challenge we can't overcome.nnAkatosh bless your wares, friend.
Is that you again? You're really still alive?nnYou have one of their heads to show me?
You will find Shilixa's minions throughout these ruins. As for the lich herself? She is likely somewhere deep in the temple, probably near her portal.
Drahir smells blood on you, walker. Are you finished?
Please don't kill me! I won't say a word!
What do you have there, <<1>>?
Not all of us Risen are on the Huntress' side. Her goals seemed reasonable at first, but lately she has been riding the edge of madness.nnWe could use your help, <<1>>.
What?
You've proven that Azura's trust was well-placed, <<1>>.

I've heard the countess is sick or something. I'd go and check on her, but I don't want to catch anything.nnIt is a shame though because I've been working for weeks to get her the perfect gifta miniature pony! She's going to love it!
This blacksmith makes quite a bit of gold. I wonder how much he pays in taxes to the countess.
Oh, it's you. I saw you leaving the countess's house earlier. nnI don't mean to intrude, but I simply have to ask. Are you yet another suitor come to seek her hand in marriage?

If the countess has truly lost her mental faculties, someone needs to take custody of the estate.nnIf called upon to do so, I would be willing to assume that responsibility, but I would not enjoy it unless she was at my side.
May the Eight protect you from the plague. Be careful.
We've got to stop these ogres or they'll overrun us by nightfall.
If the Thane has requested your aid, we'll not stand in your way.
Please, help me before that giant crocodile comes back!
I want some professionals around here. The current sentries are no good. No good at all!
Yes, this must be death. Where is the peace and serenity we were promised?nnStranger, I do not know your purpose, yet I must ask your aid. I've no wish to remain in this limbo any longer.
It is not yet time for us to strike. I must gather my forces, and your house must prepare. Without resources, we will be unable to breach the Doomcrag.
I'm glad to see you're still alive! I'm almost ready to get back in the fight  almost.nnSoon those Daedra-in-disguise will feel my blade!
<Hovering crystal is dull and cool to the touch.>
<<1>> is finally dead. The rest of these slavers will probably clear out soon.nnThanks for cleaning up the filth, <<2>>.

I should curse you mortal, for disturbing our rest, but my spirit has never been at peace.nnI've walked these ruins for centuries, cursing the king's name. My father in name, but never in action. He left me here to die.
Be careful. Be vigilant. Trust in Stendarr.
Find that coward for me. Tell him I'm going to collect what's owed.
All <<1>> wants is the money from selling the ebony in this mine. Get her that and she'll be happy.

Damned foreigners. Nothing but trouble around here ever since the duke married King Fahara'jad's daughter.nnAnd now there's a Redguard army on our doorstep, expecting the Knights of the Flame to just stand aside?
Where's Falhut? Did she run?
I hear-tell the problems at the Edrald Manor have been cleared up.nnWell, good on them.
Those orcs headed west towards the Ruined Steppe. Seemed to be in a big hurry. Looked very grim.nnOrcs can look mighty grim when they have a mind to, you know.
Your reward awaits you at the top of the tower.nnGo, and continue your fight against Molag Bal's influence wherever you find it.nnHe must not gain a foothold in this world!
This is a terrible day for the descendants of the Greatmothers and Greatfathers.
You've no idea the anguish I'm in... seeing my bones strewn about like rubbish. I can't leave
target: not with my remains in such a state.

source: Thanks. I'll help you for a few minutes, but then I've got to report to <<1>>.
Scamp skins, scamp skins, Giddy wants scamp skins.
If you die in this endeavor, we will not weep. Not for an outsider.nnSucceed, though, and my tribe will welcome you as clanfriend.

The duchess is likely in her chambers upstairs. For now, just try to win her confidence. I must speak to the duke before we take any drastic actions.nnIf you learn any more about her plans, though, let me know right away.

Be cautious in Thoda's camp. It's full of young Redguards who want to prove themselves. Do what you must to prove your mettle, but don't spill any blood if you can avoid it.nnWe have to avoid starting a war.
So Missus Nurin was going to join those crazy cultists?nnI always knew that lady was a little off. I got a good feel for people, you know?

Oh, my aching neck . I haven't been this sore in years, but freedom sure does feel good.nnThis situation was more dangerous than I realized. You went way beyond the call of duty here, friend.nnI can't adequately express my gratitude.

Still no sign of Lucas. Now we have the threat of slavers.nnIt's a good thing you came here when you did, <<1>>. I can't imagine the people in the village are mentally competent enough to hold their own.
I think Ganise is still searching through the rubble in William's old workshop to the west. nnI know it's going to break her heart, but it's time for us to move on. Tell her to come to the house.
So wait a minute. You mean the constable was actually working with the slavers?nnI'm confused.
I knew I shouldn't have trusted you. You've handed the village to its enemies on a silver platter.nnYou'll see though. You'll all see!
Please speak with <<1>>. She's just up the ramps to the next floor behind me.
Thank you for setting matters straight. My men are having their wounds treated even now. nnWe'll be back on the high seas soonwhere we belong.
I guess the next thing is start making plans to rebuild. Times like these I wish we had more childrena larger family, you know?nnI guess there's always the future.
Being tied up like this is not particularly comfortable. Release me, please.

Soon as you start talking sense, we'll let you out of there, honey.nnMy poor poor Pascal.nnI thought he was acting like a churlish teenager, but it turns out he was just under the infuence of some evil curse.

So now the constable's the one in the stocks? Go figure. I always thought he was a good guyjust acting a little crazy these last few weeks.nnI just hope it'll be good for business. Speaking of which, what'll you have?
If they hadn't snuck up behind me, they wouldn't have had a chance.
Please untie me. Then we can get out of this house and make a plan for saving my father.nnI want to make sure he's all right.
My family is whole again thanks to you.nnYou'll have to excuse me though. I need to go get Lucas ready for bed.
So the farm's all clear? Terrific. Now we just have to rebuild.nnI wish we had a bigger family. Hm. You know, my father's not that old. If we could just find an eligible lady .
Didn't I tell you to leave? Why are you back? Where is my husband? Leave this house! Leave at once!nnI can hardly bear the stress. It's just not safe here!
If the slavers come back, you have to let me know in advance.nnI need to get my sweet little chickies inside.
The lengths I go to for a free breakfast of biscuits and jam.nnMy mother can be a hassle sometimes, but it's a small price to pay to have someone else wash your smallclothes.
She cannot be dead. This cannot be real. My Lakana .nnYou! You spoke with her, didn't you? What do you know of this? Tell me!
It seems my daughter was quite taken with that Gavendien. I'll be keeping her locked in the house until she comes to her senses.nnThanks again for getting her home.
<<1>> is finally dead, but I've still got work to do.nnWe need to rid these lands of anyone who doesn't belong to the Daggerfall Covenant. Foreigners and filthy half-breeds are better off dead.
The boy's home and she's happy. Back to spoiling the poor kid.nnMaybe I can sneak away for a drink soon.
So you survived? I worried you were buried along with the ogres. For collapsing that cavern, you deserve a medal!nnUnfortunately though, General Godrun's in no condition to hand out awards.

Regardless of the outcome with this 'Dame Falhut', I do not believe it's safe for Lakana to remain in the Bretons' castle. nnI will not break our treaty by ordering an attack, but neither will I leave until I am assured of her safety.

Survivors of the Hinault Farm massacre have been wandering in, but there are still more of our soldiers out there.nnLieutenant Fairfax and his unit have yet to return. I hope they found a defensible position to hold up in.
Read his journal. It reveals everything. He's gone mad!nnGo to Her Grace, before it's too late!
Keep the candles lit while I take in the essence of these items.nnWatch them closely.
Pox and pus, your sense of honor is bad for business!nnGet gone, you. I'm treating the citizens of Hoarfrost fairly.
You shouldn't listen to his ravings.nnRemember, he's injured and in a lot of pain. He doesn't know what he's saying.
With Gavendien out of the way, I expect business will pick up.nnHe was the brains behind the group, such as they were.
Good day to set sail. My ship's repaired, and even the lighthouse has been relit. nnMaybe I'll get to Hammerfell in time after all.
The fire might have started in the barn.nnI'll meet my mother at the house. My father should have a key. Meet me there after you take a look around the barn.
Sounds like King Fahara'jad's envoy is ignoring Dame Falhut and refusing to leave the main gate.nnWe're keeping our weapons ready. This may get ugly.
You should leave now. You don't belong here!
The little devils are going to get us. Why won't Rosalie listen to me.
I'm in no shape to chase after them along the coast myself.nnMay the Divines bless your efforts, <<1>>.
Now we can finally bring in reinforcements and clear this Pact refuse off our beach.nnThank you for all you've done.

We are trapped here as long as Tainted-Heart's vile abomination lives. I could not stop what happened when I was more than a sundered spirit. nnBut I'll risk my very soul to stop this horror from being unleashed anywhere else.
I guess Constable Pascal's not in charge anymore.nnMaybe this Knight of the Flame will let me go after the slavers.
Welcome, traveler, to the Wayrest Mages Guild Hall. Do I detect some interest in membership?
I'll inform the guards. We're waiting for the duchess' order to proceed. Make haste!
I know it seems harsh, but what choice do we have? The workers are mad, enthralled, and a danger to the rest of us.
If you like, you can go to <<1>> and see the destruction for yourself.nnYou won't catch me going back to that forsaken place.
I pray for those whose minds were blinded by Vaermina's Omen.nnThose who stray from the path of law and order are truly lost.
The victims of Vaermina's treachery are in my heart and prayers.
How many lives were lost to the Fervor? Only Arkay knows.
I pray for the souls lost to Vaermina's Fervor, but also for those of the Midnight Union. Stealing is sin that demands punishment.
Peace be with those who are free of Vaermina's Omen.

This Fervor I hear word of is truly the device of a Daedra.nnTo take over one's mind? To lack any mercy or compassion for your victims? I can't imagine the cruelty others have endured at the hands of Vaermina's victims.
It's not only the prices at this market that bother me, it's the merchants. All the villagers here annoy me.nnI need to move to Wayrest.
So now we have the constable in the stocks? All the same to me as long as it draws the crowds.nnSee anything you like?
If you have no other business here, you should be on your way.
Where to captain?

I'm worried about my boys. They think because they're grown men, I can't worry about them. Ha!nnI can feel the winds of change blowing. Change can be good, but this time, it brought us the sabre cats.
This is a nice spot for watching the cats. I'll wait here for a sign that it's time to move on.nnPlease check to make sure my brother is safe.
My brother may be safe, but I want him to have a fighting chance.nnWhile you're on your way to see him, kill any of the cats you see. The sounds of them dying will be a sign of our victory.
Feel free to use the portal to return to the staging ground, if you need anything.nnYou've certainly earned the right.
Please tell my sweet Shela that I still love her.
Acrady is such a sweet fool.nnOnce all this fighting is over, I may have to marry that man!
Rumors sweep through <<1>> like the desert winds - they say the captain's spirits have escaped!nnYou have done this thing? Then now is the time to strike!
I cannot believe one of our own is behind the attacks on Duchess Lakana.nnThere must be some other explanation. There has to be.
I fear that King Fahara'jhad will not be pleased with this outcome. I will do my best to explain the circumstances, but there may be political repercussions.
This decision could not have been easy for you, and it will not be easy on Duke Nathaniel. Sir Hughes is a good man though, and I am glad he will live.

Was that Ingride and Rozenn's voices I heard out there? I'm glad they're safe. nnWe'll come down and join them by and by, but Giraud's been having so much fun, I'd hate to spoil it. He'll get tired soon.

I've been holding off these scamps for hours. It was fun at first, but now I'm feeling a little tired. nnSure would be nice to go home and sit in my chair. But I have a duty to do, and by the Eight, I'll kill every last scamp I see!
My home is in chaos. My people suffer. nnHave you come to help, or have you brought even more bad news?
Many of the spirits here have found their way, thanks to you.nnSoon, I shall join them.
You saved Thomin's life. And those of our neighbors. nnMay Stendarr bless you.
May Stendarr defend you on this final task, my friend.
Don't keep the Phantom waiting. He doesn't like it.
I think I see a touch of brutality in you. Yes. It's the eyes. nnYou enjoy spilling blood, don't you? You've come to the right place.

I was hoping you were one of the men we had to leave behind. I asked five soldiers to buy time for the rest of us as we advanced. Honestly, I didn't expect to see them again.nnWhat's that you've got in your hand, friend?
I swore an oath to protect Shornhelm. nnIf we must strike at this ancient evil to defend our home, then let us be done with it.
Be wary. I would not wish the fate of those above us on anyone.
Things in Fell's Run have mostly returned to normal, but we remain vigilant against further incursions from Northpoint and the west.
You may pass, as the dark-haired Elf was allowed to pass before you.nnBe warned. His motives and yours may appear the same, but I fear he is more than what he seems.
I'm sure Karnosis' agents will attempt to block your path.nn<<1>> and <<2>> are not to be taken lightly. Putting an end to them will be the only way we can confront Karnosis without interference.
Surely you can see the absurdity of this situation. I hope you will speak to this Sir Hughes or the Duke himself.nnPlease, tell them to let me in. I mean no harm. Ask the Duchess.
I didn't expect to see you or Verandis return, not after that display of light and magic from the spire.nnWhat news do you bring?
Princess Lakana is dead. We have failed our king.nnIf her murderer is not found and brought to justice, there will be blood.
King Fahara'jad's daughter is dead. This is a sad day for all of Alik'r.nnSomeone must pay!
The General let you leave? I thought we'd be carrying you out in pieces.nnI am glad you have earned his respect though. You are a strong warrior and always welcome at my campfire.
King Fahara'jad will be devastated. He'll want someone to answer for this.
Aren't you a surprise? <<1>> is the only foe standing between you and total victory.
<These miners are all afflicted with a Dwemer mechanism similar to that of Beltis Indoril. It appears the Kwama queen is somehow transforming the miners.>
A mange on all the harpies! I hope you can rid us of them, <<1>>.
Thanks for all you've done for us. May Kynareth guide you.
I've told you all I know. Now leave me be!
What do you want?
My blood fever poultice will be put to good use. As long as people don't know what's in it, I'm sure they won't mind the smell.
By the graves of our ancestors, we will soon have the strength to reclaim our home.
If you're looking for Trista, you won't find her here.nnMost likely, she's at Breagha-Fin. That's the big cave southwest of here.
The ancients say that the <<1>> fled, or at least her essence did.
I praise the ancients for sending you to us, <<1>>.
By the bones of my ancestors, I will go south to my kin of the horse. I will learn to ride.nnThen I will trample that Dunmer's bones to dust!
Soon, I will dance on that Dunmer's grave.nnOuch! Just give me a moment  or maybe two.
I hear you might be leaving. But you're coming back, right? An arena without a champion draws no crowds.
So, Count Hosni's releasing the captives. I hope that means back to business as usual.
Not much use taking my boat out nowadays. It would just end up getting sunk by the Nords or pulled out to sea by a leviathan or some such thing, especially with my luck.nnWhat can I do for you?
Whatever you want, make it quick.

You think to threaten me, saying you will find my messenger? I would break your face if you were a soldier. But, to me, it looks if you are little more than a poor bandit.nnTake your mewling elsewhere, whelp.
May my brothers rest peacefully.
Quickly, before the Worm Cultists realize what's happened. Stand by me and activate the recall stone to take us back to Gudrun's Retreat.
Your friends in the Daggerfall Covenant would gladly send you to Balfiera Island. They always need more reinforcements for their war. Just ask for a battlemaster in one of your alliance cities.
You've seen the Herd Mother? nnShe doesn't grant her blessings lightly.
The souls are free now.nnYou must understand that he will not stop until he has destroyed everything he once held dear. He will sacrifice everything, if it will give him more power.
I have seen what must be done. The scrolls have shown me your path.nnRestore the staff. Reclaim your soul.
I fear my brothers will be trapped like this forever. nnMay the Herd Mother protect them!
The Horsemen are among my best customers.nnGive <<1>> my fond regards, would you?

Before you can reach Shiri, you'll have to unseal the vault. You must destroy <<1>> and <<2>>. Collect as much blood as you can from their undead husks.nnThat will allow you to unravel their dark magics.
You are truly the savior of Alik'r, <<1>>. We will never forget your deeds.
You don't think I had anything to do with that, do you?
Leveque is upstairs.nnJust remember what happened to Roy.

Most farmers you can recruit are on the farms south of Northpoint, towards the eastern shore. nnBy now, they should be eager to help. I can't imagine they hold any love for the Nords who have destroyed their livelihood.
Roy was a good spy, and a good friend. I hope you can finish whatever it was he started.
I'll set aside some lilies for Roy.
It's a shame what happened to Roy. May Tall Papa guide him.
I did my best to fight them, but now death overtakes me  and after that, a fate much worse.
Even priests aren't safe in Shornhelm these days. What could I have done? What could anyone have done?
<<1>> is dead, and the wards have been restored.nnYou are a gift from the Eight, <<2>>.

I guess I should probably say "thank you". If you hadn't come, I would have stayed in there forever. nnSounds like I'm heading back to Camlorn with my brother. Not too excited about that, but I guess it's the best thing.
Offer the Ansei Wards to Tu'whacca's altar as proof that the ordeal is over.nnPerhaps Tu'whacca will hear our prayers.
Offer the Ansei Wards to Tu'whacca's altar.nnTu'whacca will hear our prayers.
<The dog whines and remains next to the Breton's corpse.>
Grenna's at the Rosy Lion Inn.
Is there something I can help you with?

I've been here far too long. We have not even entered the chamber, and I feel myself weakening.nn<<1>>, you may be our last hope. With any luck, you will succeed where I have failed. You must destroy the Lightless Remnants!
A focus is required for the ritual to work. This torchbug, born from the soil and sap of the Wyrd Tree, will seek out untainted earth.nnLet's hope the corruption hasn't spoiled the entire area.
Are you an agent of King Casimir? I thought Daggerfall had abandoned us.
Leave me. Find the captain.
Captain Aresin wishes a word with you, hero.
I'll secure the docks. Get those assassins!
Please  help me!
Go on. I'm sure you'll find that hog of a pig rooting around in the northeast alleys.
You found him! You found my wonderful little Glutton!
Be careful out there, <<1>>.

Baron Montclair has been defeated and the High King crowned a ruler in Shornhelm, but that doesn't mean Rivenspire has suddenly become safe and secure.nnI suggest you travel the roads carefully, friend. You never know what you might run into.
As soon as you catch a werewolf, meet me in the cave across the bay. nnI hate to miss the fun of the hunt, but I have to prepare the cave for our reluctant guest.

Someone better warn Felise she'll have no relief from Shornhelm.nnOnce there are fewer of Montclairs' men about, I'll see if I can fix one of these carts. I don't think Finn's in any condition to walk.
My sources said that <<1>> works with the Mages Guild in <<2>>. She traveled with the  <<2>> guards to <<3>>.nnI appreciate your help, my friend.
Don't tell her she's being watched.nnFrom what I gather, she's not the threat her father was, but the High King will never be convinced that anyone from the Ranser family is entirely loyal.
Damn bandits! The roads have never been this bad! If the Daggerfall Guard hadn't arrived when they did, I'd probably be dead right now!
I'm a little busy.nnThe Red Rooks bandits are holding hostages. They're in a house down the lane.
We have orders to clean up this nest of rats.nnGood job back there.
A runner sent word that you took care of those bandits. nnDamned good of you to help.
<<1>> filled me in on the other things you've been doing around here, <<2>>. I wish there were more around like you. Thank you.
Please don't keep the mayor waiting.nnThe longer he waits, the more he drinks.
Perhaps I was too quick to pass judgment on you.nnThese people, including my sister Olyna, owe you their lives.
Have you changed your mind already? I couldn't really blame you if you did.nnIf not, <<1>> is probably still camped out southeast of here.
You caught one. Good. Let's get him into the circle.
What a beast! Right out of my worst nightmares. Thank you for killing the horrible thing.
Thank you. It's a terrible thing to be poor. You're invisible. No one cares.
I've never seen the citizens so agitated. Even the beggars seem nervous these days.
You studied under Ashton. I can tell  the relief from gettng away from that crazy woman is all over your face. So what can i get you?
The threat to my husband was a threat to the Daggerfall Covenant as a whole.nnOn behalf of my father, King Fahara'jhad, and all of Alik'r, I thank you.
The air feels so nice out here.
I can start a new life. A better life.
I should have never left her. I ... I don't know what I'll do from here.nnHer face ... I'll never forget her face.
Gorak returned in a state of some excitement. nnI take it you saw enough action to teach him a thing or two?
I have a great deal to tell you. And a great deal to learn, of course.

Do not linger here, stranger. The fight is still in your hands. You still have much to live for. My days will end here, where they should, next to my wife.nnGo now. Do what I could not. Protect those who deserve to live.
I don't want to die! I don't want to die!
That was unexpected. Why did you change your mind?
What are you thinking, bringing that beast in here? Head to the cave before that creature breaks free and starts killing people!
This has been a harrowing experience, for all of us. We have lost allies of great worth and many people lie dead because of Faolchu. My heart is heavy, indeed.
Cultists, bogs, bugs as big as my head  why oh why did I ever leave the city?
Please, you have to help us! That magic stone keeps us bound here. Smash it! That should free us.
Do you suppose those looters made off with Gardenne's corpse?nnWhy did he put the uniform on a bloodfiend? It makes no sense, or at least, no more sense than any of this has.
Offer the Ansei Wards to Tu'whacca's altar as proof that the ordeal is over.nnPerhaps Tu'whacca will hear our prayers.
Offer the Ansei Wards to Tu'whacca's altar.nnTu'whacca will hear our prayers.
A messenger? From Aldcroft, by any chance?nnWhat news from there? We heard reports that Camlorn refugees had inundated the town.
By the Eight, why the blazes are you still bothering me?nnGo find that damn Dagger and get me back my egg.
I'm working with someone else right now. Go get your own mercenary!
This is my fault. I'm the one who wanted to sell the johads. My father deserved better than this.
Did we do it? Did we actually complete a mission? Quick, talk to Gelvin so he can explain what happened here.
The fool's got you collecting eggs, doesn't he? You do know what his lordship is doing here, don't you?
Well, that made me smile. Old pompous ass deserved every bit of it. nnWhat do you need?
A fitting end to a vile man, if you ask me. You chose wisely, <<1>>.
I'll help the others clear out. nnIf the harpies don't eat his lordship, we'll send someone back for his corpse.
I think Guy and Erwan may be back along the road, west of here.
You can find the hags to the west. Just protect that charm. It is your best defense against Mother Murk.
How did you do it? She's here with me!

Normally the Imperial City is closed to my magics. The Tharns rule there, and they have proven an enemy of the Mages Guild, and of the Moth Priests.nnThese are extraordinary circumstances, though, presenting extraordinary demands. Are you ready?
Sorry, hunter. No more bounties today.

Greetings, sandwalker. I can tell by that look in your eye  you know lizards. nnDo they speak to you? Do you enjoy the feel of their cool scales against your cheek? Yes, you understand. I know you do.
I can't thank you enough for your kindness. The pipe must be somewhere in the lighthouse or our cottage. nnPlease, be careful.
May Tall Papa bless you for helping us. Send everyone to meet me in Lainlyn. There's nothing else I can do here.
Are those walking corpses gone? They killed my brother!
My visions are a gift and a curse.

We are in your debt, <<1>>. You must kill elder firebite scorpions outside of <<2>>. Then speak with <<3>> near the entrance to the stables. He'll have another task for you.nnMay the ancestors guide your steps.

My family owes you a great debt. Go slay elder firebite scorpions outside of  <<1>>. Then speak to my brother <<2>> near the entrance to the stables.nnUntil he has the proper ingredients, my father cannot make the offering. You should hurry!
Thanks to you, the Daedric attacks have subsided.nnWe are in your debt, <<1>>.
The others, they're free. I can't leave, but what does that matter? At least Rosalind and the others no longer suffer.
Have you seen Leon? We're worried about him.
I haven't seen Leon since before the attack. I hope he's all right.
I don't know who you are or what you did here. I only know that things are  changing. nnThe spirits of Westtry are quieter now.
You glow, oddly. What's going on? Why do I hear voices?
Kill any Daedra you see in Aswala Stables.nnWith your help, maybe we can turn the tide of battle against these devils.
<This corpse was cut multiple times and mangled beyond recognition. The dead man's right hand is clutching a piece of paper.>
Now that the portal has closed, the Daedra have been confined to Oblivion again. I salute you, <<1>>!nnUse this gateway to return to the at-Aswala family. Tell them of your victory.
My husband looks so much better. Thank you for everything.
By the Eight! Whatever you gave him seemed to do the trick. I pray that the madness is well and truly over.
Thanks to you, my nightmare is over. nnIt's time to return to Camlorn.
I will be most relieved if this fellow turns out to be harmless. But we cannot be sure until he is stopped. Please, go carefully.
You've been to the Aswala Springs Cave? What did you find?
Go to Aldcroft, he says. It'll be safer, he says. I shouldn't have listened to LeBlanc.
I'm ready to go, of course, but first we need clearance from Captain Vistra.
So it did work? It was so quiet after you went in, I worried, but seeing you now, well, I feel so proud, and relieved, of course.

I believe the Eight sent you to Alik'r in this time of grave peril for a reason.nnI pray you succeed in recovering the Ansei Wards. If you don't, an army of risen ancestors will march across the land.
I hope the others are all right.
Better get moving. Stay in one place too long, the Bloodthorns'll get you.
Slaughter the Daedra beasts stalking through <<1>>. Harvest their hearts and deliver them to my father, <<2>>.nnHe's defending the tower north of the stables. Hurry, <<3>>!
See how the past speaks to us! Isn't it amazing? I almost wish I was brave enoughI mean, expendable enoughto go with you to the crypt.
No surprise there. Poor Sarvith, his spells never work as planned. nnIt's always the same. One disaster after another.
Please  don't hurt me. I didn't do anything wrong. I'm not part of the Worm Cult. I swear it!
target: Please  don't hurt me. I didn't do anything wrong. I'm not part del Culto del Verme. I swear it!

source: Ah, this armor brings back such memories. nnNow get dressed. There's much to see and the connection to the past won't last long.
Bah, don't worry about me. Just head back to the camp. nnGono time for questions.
Whatever happens, beloved, I . nnNo, enough. Only the fight matters now.
Good luck, my friend. I'll see you on the battlefield. nnNow, let's make that bastard Faolchu pay.
I just don't have time to speak to you unless you're a member of the Fighter's Guild.nnShould you wish to join, go to the Fighters Guild Hall in Daggerfall. They will get you straightened out.
You had the strength to do what no one else could and now I'm free. You have no idea what that means to me.nnBut tell me, stranger. Why did you do all of this?
You must avenge my fallen companions! Use funerary oils.to burn the living dead in the Tears of the Dishonored. Then put them out of their misery.nnWe must prevent them from ever being raised again!
Why am I so out of breath? How far have I run?
Ahh! I can smell the nasty, stinky dogpelts you have! nn<<1>> would never want them, but she knows a trader in Sentinel that will pay well for him. Flinchy, twitchy little man. Loves lizards.
Where is it? Have you found the <<1>> yet?nnI tell you, it's somewhere high up in the tower where I was imprisoned. We can't let the cultists keep that artifact!

These Bloodthorn are nothing more than graverobbers. nnTake back the regalia they stole and return each item to its proper tomb. They hide the items in the groundskeeper's cottage south of the Burial Mounds.
Sisters, let me talk to this stranger.nnWe are busy. Please make your business quick.
You are swathed in the dust of consecration. Were you able to get aboard the Iliac Rider?
You dare to approach me again? Have you done as I commanded?
You are not a member of the Mages Guild. If you wish to join us, please seek out the Mages Guild Hall in Daggerfall. They are seeking new students.
You are not a members of the Mages Guild. If you wish to join us, please seek out the Mages Guild Hall in Wayrest. They are seeking new students.
You are not a members of the Mages Guild. If you wish to join us, please seek out the Mages Guild Hall in Daggerfall. They are seeking new students.
Slay the Bloodthorns. Break their hold over our servants. nnOur servants have been loyal and true. Such commitment must not be repaid with slavery.
You've done enough for us already. Please, speak to my son and get some well deserved rest.nnI fear this isn't over yet.

Hello! You look like someone who may be interested in joining up with the Fighter's Guild. If that's the case, I'd suggest you visit the guild hall in Wayrestl. They can get you all the information you need.
The Fighters Guild is recruiting if you're interested in joining. You look like you can handle yourself in a fight. We need people like that.
Welcome back to our village, <<1>>.
I will join you at each gallows and issue a summons. The risen dead will appear to face a trial by combat.nnYou must defeat the risen skeletons of Hillid, Islaif, and Thadret. Only then can I rest.
I believe I can sense the gods returning already. I lost my faith, but you have restored it.
As soon as we've finished moving back into the manor, I'm going to plan a hunting trip. This adventure's got my blood up!
Oh, dear. You shouldn't have risked your life on my behalf.
The blasted zombies just keep coming. I don't know how much longer we can hold out.nnI hope Gabrielle finds something to help us sooner rather than later.
Lieutenant Harim's probably near the lighthouse. Be careful as you make your approach. The place is crawling with Bloodthorn cultists.
The circle is just northeast of here, up the trail along the beach. nnPlace the talisman in the revelation pool. That should force whatever's inside to come out.
The werewolves were strong, but we were stronger.nnThose who died in this fight did so with honor. They have no regrets.
We'll continue to interrogate these cultists until we've learned everything we can about Angof. nnWe must find a way to stop him.
Of all Camlorn's heroes, past and present, you may be the craziest. It takes a certain kind of recklessness to take on someone like Faolchu. You have my admiration.
Thank you so much for helping me. nnYou really are the hero they say you are.
The hag village lies west of here. Good luck, <<1>>.
Please, speak to Marimah. He's in the largest tent in the camp.nnWe need your help.
The ring? You're making it?
Be bold, <<1>>, and strike them directly.nnI'm not as strong as I once was, so I must approach more cautiously.
We are free! This is how it should be.
Thanks for your help. Have you spoken with Tamien?
I need to talk with my father. Go ahead and let Dame Clarique know what happened.
I'll make sure my brother recovers. Thank you for everything, <<1>>
You'll excuse me if I'm cautious and don't welcome you, stranger. I've lost friends this day.nnA stranger caused their deaths and all this madness.
Tell Zal at-Zazir  hard to breathe  tell him to come.
If you can't seal that gate, this will be a very short offensive on our part.
You  you're going to speak to Enneh? Thank you. I just pray that there is some explanation for this .nnIf Casnar is dead  I don't think I can go on.
You missed it! You should have seen the look on Jagnas's face when I arrived!nnIt was extremely satisfying.
I knew Casnar was having doubts, but if he decided to back out, he should have at least sent word.nnTo put his bride through this is just cruel. Poor Tiela!

My stupid brother! He's been looking forward to this day for weeks. He probably went off last night, got drunk, and passed out in some back alley.nnThe rest of my family is livid. It makes us Forebears look bad to the Crowns.

Welcome to Bergama, wayfarer! We have the finest musical instruments in all Hammerfell!nnIf you want a harp, or lute, or even a drum, you've come to the right place! Though that is not why you are here  is it?
Look at this! You walk in like you own the place, like you fear absolutely nothing.nnIf it's a fight you want, though, you've come to the wrong place. This is a place of business. I'm a businessman.
Nobody boards this ship without the captain's password.nnSpeak the password or walk away.asdssd
Still here? I tell you, it's urgent that we get to that inn. Don't you know we're out of ale?nnNow get that key.
I told you everything. Leave me be!
Ah, <<1>>! Good!nnThere is a barred door at the far end of this tunnel with more of those murderers on the other side. I want to make sure they don't get a chance to come through.
Gods, why did I agree to this?nnI don't know what's going on aboard my own ship. How can I even call myself a captain?
Who are you? Are you one of the Withered Hand or one of those Imperial dogs?
It's so beautiful! Do you see? Things have already changed. The Wyrd Tree has been restored.
We welcome your assistance. The docks are  infested.nnI'll let the captain fill you in on the details.
The Gripdjur are nothing but thugs from the Ebonheart Pact. I can't see what possible negotiations those barbarians would be open to.
I've heard some nasty rumors about those mines. Some say Daedra worshipers once used them.nnI hope nothing bad has happened.
The palace is southeast of here.
The outcasts  it's a struggle just to say their name. To think we live in such times that we need to deal with their kind.nnSep take the Ash'abah  and this "Withered Hand," too!
I always thought Zafira carried a bit of a flame for me. I just wish she wouldn't hide it so well!
Place the candles on my family's graves. nnFirst, you'll visit three humble graves. Then you need to find a great monument surrounded by an iron fence. Place the last candle there.
Do you have enough energy to heal me?
We will see that these dead are consecrated now. They will not rise again.

We stumbled upon Alinon at the church. Had been ... been researching the wolf threat. Thinks this potion can ... save the others, but has not ... not tested it.nnYou must use it ... use it on the wolves while they are injured for its effects to work.

Some of the Bloodthorn escaped. I'll send a runner to warn Daggerfall.nnAt least you stopped their rituals. I'll consider that a victory. Hopefully, that wizard you rescued can help, too. In the meantime, we have a town to clean up.
Unclawed traitor! Ildani should never have trusted you! nnYou betrayed this one. The Baandari will know. They will not forget.
Sentinel has enough trouble as it is. I'll speak to the guard captain. Make sure to recover the contraband. Without the evidence, we'll be forced to let the smuggler go.
If you're quick, maybe you can catch <<1>> before he reaches <<2>>.nnPlease help <<3>> chase him down and bring him to justice.
I chased <<1>> almost all the way to <<2>> before I lost him. If he shows up here, I'll be waiting.nnIf you find him first, bring him to justice.
Pity we couldn't save everyone with the antidote. nnAt least now we know it works. All we need are enough ingredients.
The Ash'abah will honor your name in legends.
I hope you're able to help <<1>>  find the Guardians.
Welcome to Bergama, traveler.
I'm thinking we're going to need grappling hooks. They're very versatile, you know.
I was able to give Commander Marone the slip, thankfully. The protective spells around the Redoubt should stay empowered for a while longer, while we accomplish our task here.
That was quite the satisfying sound, wasn't it?nnI could almost imagine hearing the screams of those crushed Imperial dogs.
It is finished. The earth's strength shall return now.
Well done. Now the winds will change for foul Angof.
Balance returns. Soon the Wyrd Tree will be safe.
I will assist <<1>> with his preparations. He'll need my help in the coming weeks.nnYour aid had been invaluable.
I hope that all of our friends and neighbors are safe.
Now that you've paid for a ticket, you're free to explore the gray market.nnTry not to start any fights, or that ticket won't help you.
With the might of the Mages Guild on our side, perhaps we can finally push back Montclair's soldiers and take back Shornhelm's northern district!
Without Arkay's Blessing, the mortal clay and immortal souls of our honored dead are at risk.nnThank you for taking the time to help me. My task is hardly glamorous, but it is important.
Ah, someone new to talk to. Are you here for something specific or just to say hello?
The Queen of Evermore would never allow this to happen knowingly.nnShe was always an advocate for the people of Evermore, rich and poor alike.
I hope you're able to find  <<1>>.nnI've never seen her so determined!

So you're the one wreaking havoc down there among those horkers? I've tangled with a Reachman or two in my day, and my helmet's off to anyone who charges into their ranks that way. nnDon't suppose you've come to enlist in the town guard, have you?

Welcome back, Arzhela. Good work! First, you ran this kingdom into the ground. Then you dumped it into my lap!nnNow, the two of you repay me by sabotaging my plans and destroying any hope we had of surviving the Reachmen attack!
You mean to go through with this? I suppose it's out of my hands.
Go away! We don't want any trouble.
What do you wish of us, mortal?
You're back. And in one piece. Lady Laurent has also returned in time for supper, as usual. nnAll is right with the world.
Perhaps you'll have another chance to assist me in the future. Until then, good luck to you.
You've been a great help. Over time, the remaining undead will find peace.nnMay the goddess bless you in your travels, <<1>>.
The soldier's name was Ishan. His father requested the wake be held by the inn north of here.nnThey do not know he is missing yet. Please, let us keep this between us.
There is nothing left here for this old man.nnI'll wait for my time to return to the sands.
Most soldiers are buried at <<1>>, but Ishan's family insisted he should be buried here.nnI've almost finished digging the grave. Don't fall into it.
I'll go to the altar and pray for your safety, friend. Once you have the <<1>>, we'll break the curse.nnI really don't want to spend eternity paying for a mistake I didn't make.
Finally, <<1>> put others before himself!
We need to cut down enough of these monsters to clear a path through the camp. nnThen we might have a chance to retake the city.
I'd love to join you on the attack, but these troops are green. Most of them have never fought a werewolf, so I'll need to stick with them to show them how. nnBut kill a few for me.
What? Is Queen Arlimahera here? nnYou do not look like one of her messengers. No, that was so long ago.
This place is a graveyard of harpy victims. Save who you can!
Have you spoken to <<1>> yet?nnHe'll have me doing his errands for a month if I keep this portal open much longer!
My flock has been continually diminishing. They just seem to disappear. What is happening?
The cursed crown is on the left as you enter the vault. nnGood luck, I suppose. That's all I have to offer.

See these vines? Corruption runs through them and they choke the sacred stone. Soon, they will tap into the stone's magic and defile it completely.nnIf you will help me, I can destroy these foul vines.
Corruption radiates from this  thing. I can feel it worming into my soul. The corruption spreads outward, altering or killing all the forest creatures. We have to destroy it!
I loathe these vines. They reek of death and corruption. But every time I try to deal with them, I'm attacked by cultists or corrupted creatures.
<<1>> told me you would come. I hope this works.nnPlease don't let anything happen to me while I destroy these vines.
The tunnels are crawling with the undead. Be careful, <<1>>.
It's unfortunate we were too late in warning Tu'whacca's Throne, but I'm glad you were able to aid them.
You're still alive? Well, it seems I'll have to remedy that.
You have done much to help us, but I cannot rest while the Ra Gada sergeants still roam these ruins.
I don't want to leave the prince alone for long. We'll have to be quick.
Your choices were difficult, but you have made them well.
Hopefully Queen Therese will put a stop to this.
My retainers and I will be ready to assist you at Bangkorai Garrison when the time comes.
That  that was the thing that attacked my father!

Master Barah's fall was such a tragedy. For a swordmaster to survive such a battle, but never again be able to lift a blade  I don't know if I could have borne that burden.nnThen again, Master Barah was stronger than I am.
The stables are not as busy as they once were. Still, I will care for all beasts that seek shelter within.
Have you come to  no, you're not the provisioner from Sentinel.nnI've had to send farther and farther away for simple things such as salt and grain!
Kill these monstrous creatures and avenge my fallen brethren.
When you choose for one, you choose for all. Such is the burden of leadership.
To act  to not act. Each is a choice.
A single decision can define a civilization. Think hard on your legacy, wayfarer, for even small choices can have great consequences.
Not even the grandest hero can escape regret.
What are you still doing in here? You need to chase down that monster and kill it. Kill it dead!

I've got buyers slavering at my feet and nothing to sell them.nnNo one's going to send ships up this way with the Reachmen lurking about, least of all Wayrest. They act worse than pirates  and smell worse than them, too!
Collect signet rings bearing my family crest from the risen dead in Tu'whacca's Throne.nnYou must wrest their souls from the Withered Hand's clutches. You must put my family to rest!
I'm getting out of Evermore and I advise you to do the same if you know what's good for you.
Speak with <<1>> at the bottom of this tower. nnTell him of the Dremora, and go with my blessing.
Greetings friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that. nnIf you want to join the guild, you should speak to Hareld.

Pardon my intrusion, but I would speak to you on behalf of Queen Arzhela. I am her handmaiden.nnThe queen has  heard of your recent accomplishments, and she asked me to make a private request on her behalf.

Mongrels from the Reach are flooding into Bangkorai, but what does their "High King" do for them?nnI have yet to see a response from Wayrest. I hope the people of Evermore realize we can work together t-nnWait, I recognize you.
All my life, others decided my fate. Now that I am no longer a political pawn, I'm actually enjoying myself.nnWhen I help the poor, it's not because I have to, but because I want to.

I offered to help, but she refused. Truth be told, I think she trusts monsters more than other people.nn<<1>> better be hiding among the rocks along the road through the <<2>>. If the Imperials find her, they won't be very understanding.
You shouldn't insult a visiting dignitary.nnMaster Luvian has been nothing less than gracious in his dealings with us.
I hope <<1>> isn't too disappointed.nnPerhaps you can assist him with whatever issues he's having.

Look at the crowds of peasants desperate for news of the queen.nnThey see no leadership, only politicians negotiating their freedom with the Imperials. Hungry for information, they'll listen to anyone, including those paid to incite trouble.
I think you're ready to advance to journeyman. nnYou should travel to Daggerfall to be tested.
You should travel to Daggerfall to take your journeyman test.

Greetings friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that. nnIf you want to join the guild, you should visit the Fighters Guild Hall in Daggerfall.
We have our fair share of problems with the undead around here. You might have noticed.
You seem to have mastered all the skills of an apprentice. nnGo back to Daggerfall and take your journeyman test.
My advice is to go back to Daggerfall and take your journeyman test.

Finally! The Elves came damn near ruining my entire expedition! Of course, Stibbons was really to blame. nnRegardless, I'll be glad to get back to studying the ruins instead of skulking around and trying to hide from the Elves.
Still as the stone that walks. Yes.nnThey remember, you know! They carry their histories, etched in their flesh!
I just keep asking myself, why in Oblivion would you have decided to help Stibbons?nnI have to believe that you were motivated by some deluded sense of pity. I feel sorry  for both of you.
Please, mercy! I was just doing it for the gold. I swear!nnThey asked me to cast aspersions on our queen, but what harm could it do? I've got a family to feed!
Gerric is upstairs. He has a recipe for an expert ring.
You've returned! What did you find?nnWas it jewels? Ivory? Gold?
Thank you for lifting this burden from me. My task here is done.
I can't believe poor Richard is dead. I warned him about rummaging around in those old ruins.
Blessings upon you, traveler.
Shurkul has the recipe. Talk to me when you have learned it
I'm going to make sure these people are taken care of before I leave.nnIt's the least I can do.
Do you have the ring
Antieve has the recipe. Once you learned it come back and talk with me.
Poisoned by spiders  be careful. They are attracted to movement.
I've lost track of how long I've waited here  hours, days, weeks. Who can say?
We will need to bless the voice's bud if you intend to go through with this.
What in Oblivion is he thinking? How dare this petty priest question methe chosen of Arkay? It's obviously because I've earned the god's favor and he hasn't. He's jealous!
Crush some Bloodthorn skulls for me. nnFaith and the Covenant!
You are almost done now keep on clicking!

That's it. The bud is ready. Take it to the girl, Elara.nnI can't believe Demara continues to help the Sentinel on this mad scheme. We will all suffer for his generosity in the end. The girl knows nothing of the woods, and it will cost us all dearly.
You've already earned the Test of Skill achievement. You can't earn it again.

As the Sentinel, I must warn you that these woods aren't safe. But as Old Gurles, I'm glad to see a friendly face.nnI remember when that child wasn't more than a knee's height, and now she's laid out like a corpse.
I monitor all training with the beasts of Leki's Blade.nnShould their poison become too enfeebling, speak to me, and I will cleanse you.
Have you accomplished your goal, Sentinel-friend?
I should be fine to head back soon. I just need to figure out how I'm going to skirt the witchmen on my way back through to the docks.
I don't know why we came here everything that could have gone wrong has gone wrong.
How am I any different from you, deciding who is spared and who dies?nnWhat gives you the right to judge me?
I can't believe it. You gave the tools to Tamien? How could you?nnNow I'll never get back to Lady Laurent's good graces! I still can't understandhow can she just drop me after so many years' service?
It sure is strange, this feeling. And it's time for this Viridian Sentinel to have some rest.nnLuckily for the princess and myself, I found someone to take up the mantle.
I don't know what Stenwick is planning, but if it'll save my life, I trust him. I don't understand why these Wyrd people can't see that!
I am reborn!
Don't worry about these fellows.nnNothing will get to them while I'm here.
As long as I have the tools of my trade, I can make an honest living. A good tailor is welcome anywhere!
Thanks again for helping Odei. I don't know what I would have done if I had lost him to the wolves.
I'm safe now. Thank you for bringing me here.
The queen used to love the gardens behind Evermore's castle.nnI made them especially for her, you know.
I couldn't have made it here alone.nnI hope the queen rewards you.
I have some good news and some bad news. The good news is that the people have begun to rally around the idea of resisting the Red Rooks. nnThe bad news is the Red Rooks have taken notice.
Tamien, my son. He's come back? I'd hoped I'd see him before the end. Quickly, though, there's no time. We must act!
I hope the soldiers still live. That mist is deadly. nnAnd that fool from Camlornwhat was he thinking? He charged right into the mist after them.
Yes, whatever. Back to it.
Did you teach those Red Rooks a lesson?
Gave 'em a good wallop, did you?nnThe captan's not going to like that.

<<1>> spends most of her time sleeping inside her basket. There are lots of baskets and vases around Bergama. Perhaps she's hiding in one of them.nnFeel free to kill any other snakes you find. I'm only worried about <<1>>.
Even if he could come back, I wouldn't want to see him.nnHe chose the king's service. He could have had so much more.
In Orsinium, we burned an effigy of each fallen hero and feasted until the smoke cleared.nnFor some, it took hours. For others, it took days.
The Pearl is the Way and the Guide, the light to the Far Shores and back again, placed by Tall Papa's hand.

Your keen tactical mind and honorable actions have seen us through a tight spot.nnThe Saltwalker Company consider us allies for preventing a bad contract, and you've stopped the Withered Hand cold. Well done.
If you talk to the witch, take care. I hear if you look one in the eyes, her gaze can follow you anywhere.nnAnd never lay a hand on one. Poor Stennic tried to rough one up. They never found him.
You can find <<1>> in the <<2>>, just east of <<3>>.nnKeep a light step, and may the woods will guide you.
I'm glad we're doing something. nnWhen this is all over, we'll be proud of what we accomplished against these  these  ruffians!
Heseph never gave up. And neither will I.nnI'll help Sellan rally the townsfolk. We'll make these bastards pay.

Well negotiated, <<1>>. Your keen tactical mind and honorable actions have seen us through a tight spot. The Saltwalker Company consider us allies for preventing a bad contract, and you've stopped the Hand cold.nnWe may even recruit them. Well done!
If I go one more day without a slice of cheese, I will fight my way through the ranks of the Seventh Legion all the way to Alik'r!
I'll head out and start rallying the townsfolk after you leave and I lock up here.nnNo reason to leave an open invitation to those damn bandits.
I saw Hadjara's youngest child fighting with Mirielle's daughter over a slice of bread. I hope Hadjara can earn a ration token soon or they will be kicked out of the tunnels.
These ration tokens are a good idea. It's a shame that there isn't another way to track our food supplies.
I keep my ration token close at all times. I don't want to end up frantic and starving, like Hadjara.
Hadjara had better keep her children in line. I know they are hungry, but that is no excuse to start fighting and stealing.
Meet me at the center of the graveyard. I'll be along shortly.nnRemember, I can clear a path for the soldiers, but I can't protect myself and perform the magic.
The smugglers have taken over large sections of the sewers below. When you find them, show those scum what happens when they wrong an honest citizen. There's a price to pay for such wickedness.
I must thank you again.nnHad you not discovered my body, I might have been trapped on this plane of existence forever.
The swords of the Saltwalker Militia will never belong to the Withered Hand now. All thanks to you, <<1>>.
Win the duel, and I will listen. I value two things: gold and honor.n nFor today, at least, I have the luxury of valuing honor over gold.
Begone. I have no use for self-righteous fools. Sound the drum if you wish to fight.

For a moment there, I feared my faith was already proven false. Much hinges on your involvement, but fate has decreed that you will run this race  and that you will win. nnAre you willing to test this?
We're knights, you know. Veterans. Not scared. nnBut you  be careful down there.
This poor soul doesn't have much time. His blood, it's boiling. nnThat bite must have infected him. Even Faolchu wasn't capable of this.
I've learned all I can here. Time to find Sir Lanis. nnGood luck.
You've done what I thought was impossible. Brinarch the Briar Heart is slain.nnI've put out a call to my sisters for us to retake the <<1>>, now that the Reachmen's leader is dead.

Fear not. They do not command the strength of their master. You must slay them and hope their spirit is strong enough to part with their flesh.nnThey suffer more by living than they would if they died by your hand.
I hope Sorick was happy to hear the news.nnI, on the other hand, have been passing the time chatting to our new friend here. It's rather depressing. I hope the healers get to one of us soon.
What  what madness is this? I'm once again among the living. That can mean only one thing: intruders in Farwatch.nnElves, no less? But you are no elf. What is happening here? Speak quickly!
You have disguise? You killed warchiefs for <<1>>?

You have stepped onto a predetermined path. Fate decrees a duneripper will consume your bones before the end of the day. Deny fate. Slay Istraga.nnThen bring me one of her scales as proof of your victory.
If the fortifications don't hold, then the wounded won't have time to fall back to the ships.
Very curious. <<1>> is a changed man.nnPerhaps he'll realize that with his new apparent strength and physique, he can be more than just a mere servant.
I didn't think I'd run into you again, especially out here in this desert.nnTo think I traded one life of servitude for another! I suppose it's really all I know.
Your pack looks heavy, <<1>>!nnDid you find the tablets?
Thank Stendarr you're here, <<1>>.nnThe bones of the necromancers who died at the <<2>> are giving me no end of trouble.
Hurry and speak to Zeli. She's waiting at the Shornhelm Mages Guild.
I will send word ahead of you via the Mages Guild. <<1>> or <<2>> will meet you at the <<3>> docks.nnMay Arkay watch over you, <<4>>.
<<1>>, is it? <<2>> mentioned you were helping us.nnAnd now you're in his hunting ground. I hope your luck with Hircine's game is better than mine.
What's happened? Some of the people in town are acting strangely.
Thank Stendarr, you got rid of that cursed spirit.
I don't know if I can make it, but I'll try.
