I wouldn't take on that abomination without first dealing with its totems. But I'm sure you know your business better than I do. nnDon't worry about me. I'll find Sir Lanis and the others.
Welcome to our humble village. Not many find us by accident, yet  I smell no illness upon you.nnMay I ask what brings you here, if not the cure?
Be careful in there. I'd hate to have to include your death in my report.
Please warn the Evermore soldiers about the Reachmen. They should know what happened here.
I'm still in quite a bit of pain, but I can already feel it working.nnThank you.
So ... much pain. I made the right choice, didn't I? Life as a werewolf? I know I did.
It feels ... warm. I suppose that means it working? I do feel a bit better.
Thank you for the potion. It is helping. Maybe I shouldn't be so quick to distrust these people just because of what Caithe did.
I just want to go home.
The stone! That's the stone!nnRecite the words etched on it. Be precise, for the wrong words will shatter it.
A most engaging fight, mortal. You've piqued my curiousity.nnWhat do you seek?
Your time here is complete, mortal. I expect you wish to leave, do you not?nnUnless you would like to become my newest quarry .
Speak to <<1>>, the lizard breeder. Pick me a winner!
Come, let me gauge your strengths.
<<1>> was one of our best. Her death is a blow to the guild. After all, stock like hers is hard to replace.
When you're done, find <<1>> in the center of town. He'll want to know the fracas has finally started.nnI'll let Marent know you're coming.
Came out here to find lazy bones dying on the job! I'm not having it. No one kills him but me!
<The dog whines and barks at the skull and then looks at you expectantly.>
I have many wonderful lizards to choose from.nnWere you looking for something particular?
I've been expecting you, <<1>>. Have you brought the bones of that witch, <<2>>?
The necromancers maintain my bindings.nnYou must kill them to set me free!
<<1>> sent word someone would be arriving from <<2>> with an important package. Would that be you?
So you're the <<1>> I've heard so much about.nnI trust you dealt with the necromancer's bones?
I heard you got to interrogate an Imperial prisoner! nnAnd yes, I'm still here on supply duty. I can only hope there'll be some action in this for me soon.
<<1>> mentioned she saw you out in the woods.nnI'm glad to see you made it here in one piece!
I can't believe that Nicolas is gone. He may not have been right, but he was trying to help.
Thank you for rescuing me! I'm sure I would've died back there.nnThe Withered Hand wanted to use my life force to promote <<1>> to a lich! Luckily, he couldn't fully complete the transformation.
Have you eased the suffering of the risen dead?
<<1>> is much safer with <<2>> dead. You've done a good thing.
Take care. The princess should realize the importance of the blessing she was given, not only for her sake, but all of us.
I'm sick with worry for everyone trapped down there with the Reachmen.

Stendarr wants you to go to Jackdaw Cove, my friend. You'll find the cove is closer to the Reach than we are, and it may be in more danger.nnI'm sure <<1>> will be able to clear out the Reachmen here, especially after all you've done to help.
<<1>> is waiting to hear the fates of the trolls' quarry.nnHis home is just down the road. Go speak to him.
Not Wyrd. Not ... Sentinel. Token here, but this one who carries is different.
Get back! I don't want to hurt you too!nnGods, bring the change already! I've had enough of this torture!
Still here?nnFeel free to grab a chicken of your own, if you can catch one.

King Eamond had a stableboy who  kept me informed, but I've heard nothing since the king's deathnot even word of who assumed the throne.nnHis name is Ramza. Find him and tell him I sent you to help. We cannot allow Bangkorai to fall.
Always new mouths to feed around the village. Well? What're you looking at? I'm not selling anything to anybody.
Shame about Rahannal's injuries, he'd make a good hearth-husband once he's healed up.nnThink he's interested?
You're the one who saved <<1>>!nnI can't thank you enough.
Did you stop the dancing? The prancing?
As soon I recover, I'm going to Wayrest. I have to warn the king about these people, these Supernal Dreamers.
Oh no! The fact that he is not with you does not bode well. Did you find anything? Was he dead? What about the supply pack?
Look at all those weapons!nnYou actually did it. I can hardly believe my eyes!
<<1>> has asked me to repair the broken rain catchers.nnCan you protect me while I work?
I'm going to make sure everyone gets home safely, then I'm heading straight away to Wayrest to join the Mages Guild. This affair has inspired me to study real magic!
<<1>> is in the Sentinel's care. She lies in his hut, just on the crest of the hill.nnPerhaps you will see why he has sacrificed so much for her. It is beyond me.
If you cannot restore the towers and attract Tu'whacca's grace, we will never stop Uwafa!
<The ghost glares at you and does not respond.>
<This must be the gate through which Daedra are entering the <<1>>.>

Enter the oasis and look for bite victims. If you find anyone suffering from snake venom, apply the antidote to the victims' wounds, so they can walk out of here.nnWhen you're done, bring word to <<1>> near Bergama's entrance.
When the snakes attacked, it was complete chaos. The horses ran away with the wagons  and I ran too.nnI know some of the people were bitten. I only hope we are not too late with the antidote.
The freed soldiers seem to have things well in hand on this side of the pass.
According to section sixteen of the Sentinel Docks trade regulations, this is a restricted area.nnIf you remain here for an extended period of time, I'll be required to place you under arrest.
Find my son, <<1>>, as quickly as you can. nnIf he was threatened, he would head for high ground. Look for him on the cliffs above us.
Snakes separated me from my family, and now I'm surrounded.nnIs there a clear path to the bridge? I'm scared to leave.
Ha! Did you think destroying my heart would destroy me? I hold the blessing of the Daedric Prince Hircine!nnYou will be my first sacrifice to him as a Briar Heart!
We have the garrison again!

See the product of treachery, traveler! We were guards assigned to the tower watching the pass to Craglorn.nnWhen the Imperials invaded, one of our own opened the door. He allowed them to kill us and throw our corpses from the very tower we guarded.
What news do you bring me? Were you able to locate this near-mythical sword?
You must leave this place. The sword is cursed.
Did you find Willie? Or at least his wallet?
The Red Rooks think that they're invincible, but we'll show them! We're going to rise up and take back our town!
<Even asleep, <<1>> appears to be struggling to escape.>
Go! Find the captain.nnWhen I recover, I'll head to Koeglin Village in Stormhaven.
It's getting  dark  and cold .nnPlease  save Lorelia .
All is quiet out here. nnDid you find any relics, any sign of the nereid?
The key will be passed around. Go, we will free ourselves!
Istahn is east of here, near the narrow pass leading around the side of Onsi's Breath.
That last package arrived just in time.nnWe had a few unruly guests who, let's just say, no longer have a care in the world.
I hope <<1>> managed to get out of Sentinel safely.nnI heard rumors that the docks were being overrun with the undead!
I hope <<1>> continues to prosper.nnMy own business has never been better.
The Imperials must be stopped.
If they're using a fracture in the planes, we have to close it.nnOtherwise, the Imperials will continue to summon undead.
I thank you for your compassion, <<1>>.nnI'll see that the bodies of the captain and the others are buried with full honors once the Imperials are gone. It's all I can do for them now.

The Hand's mages are using corrupted temple seals. They're drawing the consecrated dead from the necropolis. nnKill the mages on the rooftops and high bridges. Retrieve the seals and take them to the temple. Return the dead to rest.
I've already done what I can for you.nnLet me get back to work!

Glad one of us is still nimble. I couldn't get any further up the slope than this.nnIn the confusion of your violent entry and exit, they won't notice their papers were disturbed. Sometimes rowdy is better than sly.
A Baelborne always pays for services rendered.nnThis place might look like a ruin to you, but it's a part of my family. It's all I have left.
The Baelbornes must never return to Glenumbra.
You have served Baelborne well, friend. My family will rise again.

Fast and effective! Fate has blessed me with a competant ally ,as well as the good fortune to go unnoticed by these beetles.nnNow let me see what you found, and we will learn if Tall Papa continues to favor us today.

The bog is to the west, but the place is crawling with cultists and terrible hags. It's not safe.nnYou must help my people. We were just looking for a way out of Camlorn. We never meant to get ourselves into even worse danger.
I don't even know why we brought those militia peasants along. They're no good at all in a real fight.
I had hoped you would agree. I've already been rebuked by a few others, but the ruins in <<1>> are far more important than our regional bickering.nnOne of my fellows will find you inside. Good luck.
We're free! My men and I will fight the Imperials once we have worked the stiffness out of our muscles.
We're free! My men and I will fight the Imperials once we have worked the stiffness out of our muscles.

Please, I just want my husband back with me. He doesn't deserve this. None of these poor spirits do.nnRemember, use the ring on the undead of the area, but only when you think you'll be able to finish them off. I only have a short period of time.
What is it, <<1>>? Do you lack the courage to wield my legacy or are you just trying to annoy me?
Your prowess is known to us, hunter.nnSo why do you linger when there are beasts to be slain?
We don't get many folks from the outside. Kerbol likes it that way, and truth be told, so do I.
I don't have time to chat with you all day.nnIf you need more information, go speak with the mayor.
Speak to me when you're ready to start the event.
My story was a little out of the ordinary, but I guess not everyone here is an innocent victim. And really, life here hasn't been so bad nn except for the rash I had that one time.
You were able to hear the voice of Hermaeus Mora?nnThat's unfair. I worked my whole life for such an honor and I hear nothing.
Before you go, mortal. I have something for you. A gift, one might say.
We've done it! Victory is ours this day.
<<1>>  the stone, is it safe?nnI could not bear it if it were destroyed.
Thank you. I felt I couldn't leave knowing he might be still be alive.nnHelp him, traveler.
Thierry was the best of us. He sacrificed himself for a greater cause.
<<1>> was a good soldier. There's not many left these days.
Thank you for saving us. We'll soon head north toward Evermore  and hopefully, toward safety.
The Imperials captured us on our way to the old tower to see my father. We would all have surely perished, if not for your help.nnSomeday, I hope to repay your kindness.
The man practically walked into our camp! The sorriest excuse for a Red Rook bandit I've ever seen.nnNow if we could just get him to tell us something useful.

I don't advise travel through Rivenspire at this time, Stranger. As if the usual array of uglies that'd kill you here weren't bad enough, now we have House Montclair vying for power, ambushing my soldiers.
Thank you. I wish you well on your journeys, traveler.nnMay the Eight guide your steps.
Go! Find the captain. nnWhen I recover, I'll head to Koeglin Village in Stormhaven.
Get my family back here safely. I'll tell you exactly where the meeting is happening and how you can disrupt it.nnBut first, I need to see my family with my own eyes.
The sooner we discover the Dominion's plans, the better. nnInfiltrate their camp, locate their commander, and retrieve any messages you find.
Climb the tower and use the storm rune to put out the signal fires. nnQuickly, now. I'll meet you down on the beach after the job is done.
I saw the other scouts run up the stairs toward the tower. nnWatch out. The place is crawling with Dominion troops.
<<1>> is to the northwest. It's a short journey from here.
Thank you, stranger. Make sure the dead rest well tonight.nnMy brother and I have cared for the Barrows for years  but I've never seen desecration like this. It's horrible.
I can't believe they're dead.
Good work extinguishing those signal fires. nnYou were clearly in time. There's no sign of an impending Dominion attack.
Alas! Yet again, I mourn for the defiled hel ra and hel shira, my brothers and sisters-in-arms!nnI must savor the death cries of the necromancers you've slain.
My bones know warmth once more, and darkness no longer cloaks our path.
My bailiffs and I will keep an eye out for any more trouble coming out of Northpoint. I just wish we knew why they did this to us.
Blood-sucking bastards came out of nowhere. We did what we could.
I curse the Imperials for defiling the heroes in the necropolis!nnI cannot rest among my ancestors while they are so close and so intent on destruction.
<<1>> was a strong foe, <<2>>. You did well.

Before we can use <<1>>, the area needs cleansing. The Reachmen set up three totems to Hircine. This is offensive to Stendarr as <<2>> is dedicated to him. Destroy the totems in Stendarr's name.nnMeet me in the farms' chapel when the totems are gone.
Talk to my brother and offer to escort him.
The blood! It won't come out! nnWhat  what are you doing here? Captain Janeve needs your help! She chased Tainted-Heart to the southwest along the river.
The bad ones are still here! I can hear them thinking! I can! Make them go away. nnThey want to take me to <<1>>. Mother is scared.
Ah, you've returned. I assume this means that Leonce will trouble us no longer? Well done!
My comrades lived when I last saw them. As I  retreated.nnPlease, you have to help them. I won't give up the totem I found until I know they're safe.
Reinforcements are on the way. With the additional men, we should be able to clear out the remaining bloodfiends in Moira's Hope.nnThank you, traveler.
I'll be all right in a moment. Go light both watchtowers as quickly as you can. It's the signal my people await!
That wyress over there looks injured.nnI need to get back to Evermore to make my report, so I can't stay to help. However, you might be able to do something for them.
Do not disturb the Fires! My servants will boil your corpse in a kettle and lick your bones clean. Listen to me! I am <<1>>!
Did you find Willie? Or at least his wallet?
It won't take me long to heal in this form.
I'm not sure how much longer we can hold out against the Reachmen, but at least some of these people made it safely to the windmill.
Take that  her  body to the upper balcony. I guess that's what all those harpies are up there waiting for.
Please, hurry to Brother Rodric. The plight of <<1>> grows more desperate with each passing moment.nnA great evil rises up to devour us! May Stendarr guide and protect you from it.

Nuwarrah's family has alway been a thorn in my side. Now that I helped save the city, she'll probably host a feast in honor of the deed.nnThat could mar my reputation with the Thieves Guild. That woman is impossible.
Ugh, that hagraven's stench clings to every inch of this place. What a horrid creature.nnRashan left for Evermore, and I wanted to make sure you're all right. Where's <<1>>?

Constable Agazu is usually patrolling the town square. If you want to help, go talk to her. I'm just a bailiff.nnOtherwise, please move along. I have my own duties to perform and I need to get back to them.
Don't listen to their Orcish lies!nnThey'll say anything to get you to believe their pathetic complaints.
Thank you for rescuing the townsfolk, friend. Many of my brethren are still missing, but at least a few of them are home, safe and sound.
I do apologize for that bit with the raven. It was exceptionally meaty, and I couldn't pass up a chance for fresh game.nnHmm. I wonder if the other one is still outside.
My soldiers tell me the garrison commander, <<1>>, might still be alive inside.nnPlease rescue him. He's an invaluable tactician and, more than that, a great man. We need his help to win this war.
<<1>> is our last living child. He ran off when he was a boy, looking to find riches and adventure and other such rubbish.nnI'm glad he didn't forget about us.
I barely escaped those Imperial thugs. I'm terrified we'll run into them again. If I do, I bet they'll do more than break my arm next time.nnHow I wish my mother and father were here!
His wall is down!nnIf he puts up another shield, come to me. I will take it down.
So much for his wall of souls! Should <<1>> summon a horde of undead, come to me. I will destroy them.
If you are need of healing during the fight, come to me. I will do what I can for you.
If you need protection from King Eamond's spells, come to me. I can protect you.

I'm worried about my father and brother. They think because they're grown men, I can't worry about them. Ha!nnI can feel the winds of change blowing. Change can be good, but this time, it brought us the sabre cats.

With the horses calmed, my boys should be able to reassert control. Apples will do the trick. Radava makes regular trips to the orchards. In fact, I think she just returned from one.nnAnd thank you. You've already proven yourself a friend.
Watch out, friend! The harpies are beasts, but they're cunning. Every time I went to attack one, two more would rush to aid it.
It's bad enough to kill us and drive us from our homes.nnIt's worse still that the sorceress is defiling the graves of our ancestors!
That flash of light was blinding! My eyes still haven't fully recovered.
I swear I just saw a handful of tigers run past, fleeing for high ground.nnWere you successful?

The Seventh Legion is better armed and better organized than the resistance, I expect.nnIf one of those were to change, it'd only be a matter of time before they were driven out like the dogs they are.
<<1>> owes you its freedom. May Tall Papa guide your way.
Everyone has to make a living somehow. You go now to make yours and leave me alone with mine.
The gods smiled upon our family when they brought you to our town. May your paths be easier from now on!
This is your doing? You freed my daughter?
If you're ready, I'll take us to Evermore.nnWe must inform the Daggerfall Covenant of the threat that awaits them.
If you are a guest of Lord <<1>>, I cannot stand in your way.nnYou are free to come and go as you please.
Interrupting the Council of Kings is no mean feat. For decorum, I will ask you to speak to the queen in my stead.nnI'm afraid my presence will not be welcome here.
<<1>>! I was not expecting to see you here. This is not the most  appropriate time.nnMy apologies, my lords. Please give us a moment.
Good work! Thomas should be out by the beaches south of here.nnWatch your back.
<This woman is not breathing.>
Chirane will get exactly what he deserves.nnYou've done us a great service, friend.
I don't have all day. Get back to work and bring me my items!
Who are you, and how'd you get in here?nnAre you with <<1>>? This was her doing, but she's already paid the price for that. Leave at once!
May Tall Papa be with you on your task, <<1>>.
I pray for your success, <<1>>.
May the Eight watch over you, <<1>>.

<<1>> has caught us at a most unopportune time, I'm afraid. nnI've sent his list ahead to the merchants in Evermore. They should be able to procure the items he needs. As for the book, we have that in our library, if you wish to fetch it.
Were you able to find anything out?
Perhaps by the time you reach him, I'll have regained some of my strength.nnWhatever his need, I will try to send aid to him and his own.
Have you found Captain Balmont?nnHead directly north through the farmlands, and you'll reach the road. She should be near there.
Did you find him? I hope he was all right. nnI finally feel as though I've made an effort around here.
What did you find on his body? Anything of import?
Got a boat if you need passage. Can't go around Tamriel, but I can get you to the fishing ports about here.
There are deep waters beneath Hallin's Stand. The Imperials disturbed them, don't you think?
Ah, I probably yapped too much about Master Luvian's business. Be a friend and don't mention I told you, huh?
<With it's central gear restored, the clock is ticking away.>
Suna ye sunnabe  you are one of the slave race. How curious.nnNevertheless, I will listen to your petition. It has been too long since one has come seeking my knowledge.
Tu'whacca be praised! You turned up!nnI don't know how much longer those soldiers will last out there alone.
<You notice a drawer in this desk is now slightly ajar.>
You need to know something about our village before you go any further.nnI should've told you sooner, but I was afraid of how you'd react. Please, whatever you do, don't kill me before I can explain.
Wow. You've done a great job clearing our fields!
The dead of Crestshade  they know they have a champion. They will be with you, forever.
I hope you're here to help. We're losing ground to Covenant forces.nnWe have to hold the line here, or they'll push us back to Ebonheart and take all of Zabamat.
You're not one of these cursed Daggers, and you're not one of ours. Who are you?
This is the coral's begetting placeits nursery, if you will.nnI erect the spine of welcome. You don't look like an egg-crusher.
Follow me or meet me there. Your choice.
Holgunn said you were reliable. I trust his instincts.nnAnd I know there is much work to do.
We've been lucky to have you with us. With your help, you've renewed our confidence in this war.
All this time I've been saying we needed more men. Turns out all we really needed was you.
They are brave, my acolytes. Now it comes to me.nnOur blood will be the water, our bones the soil.
Go well along the river. And beware the ashes that dry your scales.
I'm always looking for fresh warriors to mold.

Got blades of all kinds, friendsome stronger than others. nnYou want some advice? Leave them flimsy-arse scimitars to the locals. Get yourself a bastard sword. They're strong and trustworthyjust like me. Ha!
Someone needs to do something about these damned Imperials! I wish the Guild would let me fight. They speak of neutrality in times of war. It's absurd.
Always happy to share what I know.
I suppose I should think about closing up shop. The Imperials didn't give me much trouble, but these Redguards  they might take umbrage at the decor.
These Imperials are a cursed nuisance! If they do anything to delay my deliveries, I don't care what the Guild says, I'm going to lay the fire on them.nnJust see if I don't.
Daimbert keeps complaining about the Imperials, but I'm just happy they've left us alone. nnIf there's anything I can help you with, just ask.
Welcome to our station here in <<1>>. What can I do for you today?
When you're as old and experienced as I am, no one questions your judgment. Whether that's wise on their part or not, I'm not going to argue.
I can't wait to see what Ufa has planned for these Imperials. Sounds like it will be a good time for all involved, unless you're one of them.
It's too bad these Legionnaires didn't carry more coin.nnSome folk might frown on looting the dead, but I'm not one of them.
I still can't get used to this blasted sunlight. And nothing grows here.nnThe first thing I teach my students? Move where the food is.
You're no milk-drinker, friend. It took steel to go out and do that. nnWith those bound ghosts, Davon's Watch won't fear an invasion again.
I must gather my thoughts before I go to Davon's Watch. I have to report my own brother for necromancy.nnBy the Three, I must be strong.
Amazing. This is what it takes to get the Dark Elves working with the Argonians? An erupting volcano?
That was interesting logic, <<1>>.
<You find an arrow carved into the wood of the lamppost.>nn<This arrow points north.>
<You find an arrow carved into the wood of the lamppost.>nn<This arrow points south.>
<You find an arrow carved into the wood of the lamppost.>nn<This arrow points east.>
<You find an arrow carved into the wood of the lamppost.>nn<This arrow points west.>
<You find an arrow carved into the wood of the lamppost.>nn<This arrow points down.>
Be welcome here, in the nursery of the coral child. You do not have the look of one who crushes eggs.
Can you feel it on your snout? The thunder is building. I believe there are others in the Ashlands who could use my skills. nnMay the cool rain touch our scales again, traveler.
It's almost funny, I've never seen Father frightened before. He even corrected great Vivec once!nnThank you again.
Thank you again, traveler.
The wind bears the scent of burning metal. I fear there are darker days ahead.
Travel to the northwest and look for Covenant activity.nnFind out why they're here and what they're planning. Go swiftly, and go carefully.
Have you dispatched Ahknara, that piece of n'chow?
I'm done with the Covenant. I've lost too many friends. I'm too old for this.nnIf I make it, I'm going to hang up my sword in Cyrodiil and become a farmer.
A small army stands ready to attack to the north while we're waiting for a second army to flank us. Meanwhile, assassins creep through the fort.nnThese two weeds share a root beneath the surface.
Please, go back to the chapter house now! You must try to save <<1>>.
Grab some flasks of blinding light on the second floor of the command building. They can be used to reveal the assassins.
The Brothers of Strife are too dangerous. I'll keep this from everyone who might want to use it  even Tanval.
Did I just see what I thought I saw? Did <<1>> just merge with that coral thing? Somehow, she's keeping the coral alive. nnNow we just have to deal with the witch who tried to kill it.
The heart is yours, yet the coral lives. Once I saw it was dying, I had no choice but to join myself with the coral. nnWe are one now. It's not where I expected to end, but these roots go deep.

You must find the remains of those who died fighting the Akaviri. I understand their anger. Imagine dying so close to a blessing of perfection, but missing the touch of Vivec!nnAnoint their bones. Put their spirits to rest.
So much work to do. I can't let this mine sit idle forever.
Missing daughters and erupting volcanoes? This town has seen far too much excitement if you ask this Nord.
Ah, blood and fire, haha! Now, that's what I call a happy ending.
I'll just  wait until my knees stop shaking.
<<1>> should be told that our ritual was a success.
Have you found my sisters yet?
Khralek is dead and our spirits are free.
You have medicine? Please, I'll try anything.
Find the captain. Tell Hjolm I was unable to find any Covenant troops while I was scouting to the west.nnHe should be somewhere along the road east of the fort.
Speak to whoever you want. The kinhouse is more concerned with the coming plague than searching for people who probably just ran away. But I'm sure a councilor will hear you out.
Heard you helped Vartis near the mountain pass.nnWell done. He's one of our better scouts.
This is ill news. But Mournhold will be glad to get it before the Orcs establish a foothold.
Back in Skyrim, mountains know their place. They don't explode and endanger our daughters. Pfah!
<You've taken the contents of this chest.>
You have his inheritance? That's something he'll certainly want to receive. nnI'll send word out to get his location, and then I'll send a special courier to ensure this gets to him.
I'm sure my mead-sodden spouse is around here somewhere.
Dumac take the Vereansu! Did they have to destroy everything?
We Dark Elves thought ourselves unassailable in Stonefalls. Now the Covenant stands at our gate, threatening to burn the barn and scatter the guar. nnInteresting how the past repeats itself.
You're back. I hope you're here to tell me that my people are just imagining things and everything is fine.
She did it for me, you know. She stood up to the Covenant soldiers because they wanted to, you know, touch me.nnIf she had died .
You'll find <<1>> in one of the caves with his sons. Poor man.
How have you fared? Did you recover the Sacred Thumb?
You will be remembered in this village for all you have done.
Be careful.
I mourn my brother, but I do not regret what you had to do.nnThere will be no blood-feud between us.
Let us begin. The Nedes will rue the day they heard the name of Balreth!
It is time. Pray at the brazier. And then stand back.
I'm glad the Othrys family survived. Without them, we'd be out of work.nnI only hope we can hold out until reinforcements arrive.

The death of Lady Saalu is a terrible blow to the Othrys clan. But Lord Garvas is strong, and so are his children. They will hold their chins high and proud as they set her corpse in the household ash pit.
Why try to mend what is already broken beyond repair?
Go, friend. Find the troops at Ash Mountain.nnI'll just wait here until they don't notice me, and then I'll make a break for it.
Speak to my son, <<1>>, outside the manor house. Offer to help find Bjorick.nnI couldn't bear to lose another son.
Speak to my lord, <<1>>. He's at the manor house north of here, just past the windmill.
Kill every Goblin and spider you meet. If you can distract them, I can slip past and rescue Bjorick.nnMeet me here when you're finished.
My bell got rung a bit, so I'm just going to sit here for a while.nnMeet me on the north road when the deed is done.
Your attack on those vermin was heroic.nnYou made them regret the day they left their stinking dens.
You've acquitted yourself honorably.
I would prefer you leave. I have no desire to work with those affiliated with Nilas.nnGood day.
I have nothing for you here.nnSend Nilas my regards, and please go elsewhere.
Why should I sell anything to you, dungheap? Begone!
Your money is no good here. I want no business with anyone involved with Nilas.nnGood day.
You've learned what I knew. Once again, Mavos Siloreth's brilliance will bind Balreth. Where would the mages of this age be without me?nnNow stop meddling with my eternal rest.
Good. If we're lucky, we'll survive the next step.
My sons are safe. I'll scold them for getting injured later.nnAnd my wife and daughter are safe too. I'm in your debt.
With the shalk gone, I can make a run for what's left of the farm.nnGo! Find my family. And be careful.
Looks like it's safe. Please, find the rest of my family.nnI'll make a run for the stead now. Good luck.
At Davon's Watch, you helped put the Covenant to shame, but one battle does not win the war.
Have you shown Indoril the cost of his victory yet? Get a move on. nnKill the skeletons that have risen from our dead soldiers. Take their insignia. Give their families some peace.

The nobles seem determined to send you to your death. Surely you don't expect to fight through Lord Montclair's soldiers to get to his stronghold?nnI can show you an easier, if dirtier, way to get to your destination.
Welcome to the Dusklight Inn. Not exactly the lap of luxury, but we try to make our customers comfortable. nnThe cost of a room's cheap, and if you're as broke as I am, that's all that matters.
<<1>> reminds me of some of our holds in the Rift. This place is much grander, of course. But just like here, there's always some milk-drinker trying to break down our walls.
Hold! What's your business? In case you haven't noticed, friend, we're in the middle of a siege.
I've gathered some of our most skilled fighters here. We're poised to infiltrate the fort as soon as the way is open. nnYou're the perfect fit for my plan, my friend.
The guar must've liked the way you smell. Good noses on guar, yes?nnAfter all the years I've spent around these pools, all I can smell is sulfur.
If you so much as breathe on me, I will feed you to the snakes. I have had my fill of outlander men.
You are named clan friend of the Mabrigash, and you are welcome in the Vale.

The guar are all over the pools. Don't forget the harnesses. Can't send them home without harnesses.nnI'm just going to sit here until I can't hear the screams in my head anymore. I'm sure it won't be long.

Ha! Can you believe that? I heard what Martin said. He's either completely delusional or incredibly naive. nnHe's been a troublemaker all his life, and he's not getting out of those stocks anytime soon.
Othrenis is so big, and the undead are everywhere.nnI'll never find Eanen's tomb.
Have you seen my damned apprentice? The boy's later than usual today. With my luck, he's probably gone off and gotten the plague.
I'm quite the performer, don't you think? nnGo. Tell her I'm here and that I still love her. Oh, the look on her vapid, trusting face!
Eanen, you were always too casual with the commoners. Your dalliances could still stain your reputation. nnAnd what is this Ashlander doing here? Shouldn't she be gone?

Where's my husband? By Vivec's beard, if he's drunk and passed out somewhere, I'll leave without him. That no good, useless, piece of kwama cuttle!nnOh, hello. You haven't seen my husband around, have you?
I heard you helped silence those miserable apparitions. I wasn't sure how much more of that wailing I could take. Frelie almost found herself short another sword.

I'm glad you came our way. Reges told me we've you to thank for the regained peace and quiet around here. Now maybe business will pick up, and I won't have to be concerned with looking for another job.
I'll shed no tears over the death of that traitor, Rhavil. nnHe caused us so much grief, and for what? A few gold coins from the Covenant?
Let me guess. You read the letter.nnYou're going to leave me with this crazy woman, aren't you? Curses on you and your family!
That letter should convince Ralden that he needs to act.nnWe have the same goals. Remember that. Stay out of my way, and everything will turn out fine.
I can't believe it. Rhavil!
Your offering pleases me.
I'm glad you're able to help <<1>>, but you'll need to hurry. I fear the curse may spread.
The Telvanni are the last source of power and comfort here at Heimlyn. Our duty lies here, but I sense yours will take you elsewhere. nnWalk with the Three.
Hurry into the vault. There's no telling what the Withered Hand have planned.
The Mabrigash are still suspicious, but the wheels of commerce are turning.
You performed a great service, citizen.nnWe'll handle things from here. Move along.
You chose a most difficult task. How have you fared?
The Three favor you for keeping Aerona safe.nnI don't really understand what happened in there, but Aerona says you saved us all.
My vengeance is sated.
I'm still not feeling well, but after seeing what happened, I'm sure it isn't the plague.nnI just need to rest. Thank you.
What a disaster! They were accelerating and strengthening the plague, not curing it.nnThere's a silver lining here, though. Now House Redoran knows the Maulborn are up to no good.
With the ritual disrupted, things should quiet down quickly.nnI won't move from here. I promise!
Unless the Duke himself tells me to make an exception, the library is off-limits.
Star wanders around in front of the kinhouse. Follow her. She'll take you where you need to go.nnBut don't get too caught up in this foolishness.
Please, speak to the others. You'll see that we're committed to recovering our missing family members.nnI'm going to get my egg-sister back.
You have to forgive me. I don't trust you. There's only one way for you to earn that trust.nnWe need weapons to rescue our people, enough to launch a full assault.
Those are big rats! They should do nicely.nnTake them to the door and let them loose. Then we wait. It should be entertaining to watch what happens.
Slit their throats. Throw fireballs at their heads. I don't care. Just get rid of the Maulborn.nnWhile you're out there, I'm sure you'll find something about the Llodos plague.

Giron wanted you out of Narsis. You need to get back there and find out why.nnDon't worry about those crates. The substance is diluted by now. If they ever find a way to strengthen the plague, that's when you should worry.
Any sign of Giron or Ralden?
Troubled spirits linger upon the Coiled Path.
Come back anytime. The keg's got brothers.nnShh! Don't tell the locals. When we bring them across the border, they get taxed as imports. As if we'd sell good mead to the likes of them!
We'll make sure these people receive care.nnWhen you have a moment, return to Narsis and speak to Naryu. She has a lead on the name you uncovered. I'll join you as soon as I can.
I'll gather the guards and we'll meet you there.nnGood luck, my friend.

For centuries those wishing to gain skill in martial combat have made pilgrimages to the Warrior Mundus Stone.nnActivating this stone will apply the Warrior boon and remove any other boon. Are you sure you wish to recieve this boon?
Light  the  flame  wells! nnHurry!
Not all Dark Elves are lightweights, eh? Ha ha ha!nnGood on you, friend. Come back and drink with us any time.
Malooc's spit! I was too late. While I prepared the antidote, Marimah succumbed to the poison. Always putting his tribe above himself!
Well, the curse is somewhat contained here.nnMaybe you can snuff the thing out at its source.
I'm grateful for your help. Those fumes were terrible.
I'll never forget your kindness. And I'll never do anything like this again.
Again, thank you. House Redoran would find a good friend in you.
Did you find any clues? Why would someone would poison Deepcrag Den?
I think my scribs have taken a shine to you, friend!
I am still waiting to see that ring of yours.

I fear I've done terrible harm to the morale of my people in Ebonheart.nnI'll do all I can to convince them to work with House Dres. They've been constant in their defense against the Covenant invaders.
Almalexia's blessings, outsider.
My assistants are resting and recovering now. Thanks to you, we didn't lose a single one.
Your aura portends a great destiny. Go and fulfill it.
Ah, I understand now. You must defeat the <<1>> to break the curse.
All is now clear.nnYou must defeat the <<1>> to break the curse.
It was a pleasure meeting you. Thank you for what you have done for us.
Tell Sildras what the Poet has said. Vivec says change only occurs.
The Master is confident Sildras can bear his burdens. Tell him.
The Mother attends to greater threats and relies on Sildras to care for her children. Make sure he knows this.
Good, you're still alive. Scout Mamyne told us she sent you into this cave.nnVaron says he knows you from Narsis. He and his ally have offered their assistance.
Keep your nose clean in the fortress, outsider.
He's up the road. He could be coming this way.
We can't let the plague get into Mournhold. Think of all those people!nnYou must get those shipping manifests.
You'll need to deal with my friends and get the items I want. I may want a Foozle or I may want a Woozle. Who knows!
The sword is still here, radiating a great evil, and in general just being a bit bitchy.
Don't mind me. At least I can almost walk on this leg.
Report to Captain Noris. We're on the verge of losing Vivec's Antlers.

Our warriors guard the huts where the cultists are trapped. Unbolt the cellar doors to gain access.nnSo far they've refused to see reason. If it must come to blows with their lieutenants, I understand.
Our stock is a bit low, but I have a few items. A new shipment should arrive in a few days.
Missing Argonians and murdered Dunmer are one thing, but when one of our leaders goes missing, that's quite another.nnThe other vicecanons can't ignore this.
Gods, it felt good to bury an axe in their throats! From the prisoners trickling out, I trust you enjoyed yourself as much as I. Did you free them all?
I heard Ruvali scream. She said you chased it down here. nnI took a swing at it, but it got away.
If you see Tiril, tell him I'm looking for him.
You're the one who killed the Worm Cult's lapdogs. <<1>> told you the Worm Cult stole the <<z:2>>, yes? Once they discover its secrets, they'll enslave our entire village.
Is it done? Is <<1>> defeated?
Your service to House Dres and Kragenmoor will be remembered.
Eternal life is full of advantages. No need to pull your blows when training.nnWhat do you need, stranger?
He claims a Cat-Man can know sorrow. I should pull out his tongue.nnCan a mudcrab mourn? No. When you kill their brood, it's nothing to them. But when they harm someone you love .
<<1>> presides over the Trial of the Mind, the first challenge. He'll administer the trial to any supplicant.
The power of the Zaht stones is unknowable. Perhaps now Hissmir will be safe.
It's not far. <<1>> keeps a fire burning. You can't miss it.

Hissmir is safe, thanks to you. Come back next year and share a bowl of Hist sap with me. No sooner, or your tongue will rot, your teeth dissolve, and your eyes cloud over with the milk of blindness.nnI joke. Your tongue won't rot. Ha!

The mercenaries only make things worse with the Dark Elves. Better if Stormhold is one happy family.nnAnd if you plan to start a family, might I suggest a vial of powdered kagouti horn for heightened potency? No? Your loss.
Prices posted on the board. Savings, savings, savings.
You ensured Hissmir's survival. Now we can avoid the horrors of conflict with the Aldmeri Dominion. We'll tend to the pilgrims and the Hist, as we always have and always will.
Master is back. She was gone, and I was free. But now she's back, and I am bound again.
I am still waiting to see that ring of yours.
I am still waiting to see that ring of yours. Impress me!
If you wish to wait, I am sure I can find that soul gem.
Got a prime mess here to clean up.nnAt least those mechanicals are staying inside the ruin.
What can the Mabrigash do for you, outsider?
Are you really taking instruction from <<1>>?nnLook, I don't want to speak ill of a Grandmaster but  if she starts waving a soul gem at you, run. Run, and don't look back.
Have you done as Ra-shadda asked?
Please, take that shield to my brother Mjoln. He's in Iliath Temple.nnThen I can go to Sovngarde in peace.
I must get to Sathram.
You know if you want to wait I am sure I can find that soul gem.
There is an Argonian village to the east called Lukiul Uxith. I will go there. nnLast-to-Water will never forgive me, but at least he is free.
I hope you fall into a pit of guar dung.
Thank you for your service.
Gods, why did I ever set foot in this stinking pit? Was it duty or stupidity?nnCome to mock me like the rest, have you? Well, fear not. I have no dignity left.
Are you preparing to make the ring, apprentice?
Those wards keep the Maulborn from getting infected by their plague. nnSmash them. And may the plague take them all.
We've all seen what you can do. Not looking for any trouble, stranger.
I don't like the way these mer are looking at me.
We'll keep a watchful eye on our relics. But won't that make them seem valuable to thieves?
Normally, I'd say gold is gold, but when someone tries buying my town, I get nasty.nnNever liked Khajiit anyway. Nothing but mangy fur and lice. Not clean, like proper scales.
I've given you what you need. Leave me with my prize. Many days of pleasure ahead.
Captain Doronil made me his second-in-command. We'll have Tal'Deic Fortress in top form by week's end!
Superb work. The Pact stands strong thanks to people like you.
Don't just stand there with your mouth open. You're attracting flies. Speak!
Gah! Don't kill me! Someone, help!
I'll leave <<1>> by tomorrow morning. I want no trouble.
The northeast road always used to be safe. Now that you've stopped those Dominion murderers, perhaps it is again.
On your way, forester apprentice. Next step is journeyman. Learn more recipes. Craft more gear.nnGot some for sale, if you want. Luck in the trees.
Keep your skills sharp, outsider.
I saw how you put those Sentinels in their place. Thanks!
The eggs will allow me to perform a ritual that may help to calm the Gulchcoils.
In two decades of soldiering, this is the worst ground I've ever been ordered to defend.
Tread carefully along the Coiled Path.
Thank you, I can make it from here. You have a good heart. nnI think <<1>> will be pleased with you, even though you didn't finish your path. Find him to the southeast.

We'll quit this place soon and disappear into the wastes again. The housemen will hunt us. They always do, but they won't catch us.nnBid farewell to Tirinaat, if you wish. May your kills be quick and many, traveler.

Kaoc! Right under my snout. Kill her and any of her thugs in your way.nnAnd don't get greedy. Don't try to sneak off with that Dominion paychest. That's mine! It's my payment for freeing your Dark Elf friend.
I'm not afraid. Life without Eroni is empty.
I hear you're the one to thank for finally doing something about all this. Some of us appreciate it.

It appears I owe you an apology, as well as my gratitude. My behavior was uncalled for. It's just that my wife  she was all I had. nnThanks to you, they've released her body, and we can finally return to Mournhold.
You're back. The wasps weren't too much trouble then?
I can't believe it. The Dominion is in Stormhold.nnAnd they were right under our noses the entire time.
Yes! The dead will guard us forever!
You should have taken the keystone, there is nothing left for me here except for these statues. I built them to remember my people, so I could have someone to talk to .
You must make haste, esteemed leader. If the Dominion troops leave with their treasure, <<1>> will be very unhappy indeed.
It's not every day I get a chance to dissect a Dwarven resonator. Powered by minor soul gems, you know.
We're in your debt, my friend. WIth the Dominion exposed, the ugly rumors of Argonians preying upon Dark Elves can be put to rest.
It's all going wrong. The cycle has begun anew with hate and bloodshed. Curate Brethis wanted peace, but the others  I had to run.nnWhat happened in the cave? Where is the Ashkhan?
Hmm. Looks like it's back to the drawing board.
You must hurry! Dolril will be dead and the relic will surely be stolen if you don't act quickly!
<<1>> was one of our best. Her death is a blow to the guild. After all, stock like hers is hard to replace.
Patience is a virtue  but one I'm truly lacking in! Heating ingredients to the perfect temperatures, waiting days for a poultice to set . Sometimes it's just too much!
Welcome to our station here in <<1>>. What can I do for you today?
When you're as old and experienced as I am, no one questions your judgment. Whether that's wise on their part or not, I'm not going to argue.
Knowedge itself wishes to be free. When I spoke to Hermaeus Mora about that, he - it - was quite clear on the point.nnAnyway, the former owners of these books can prove nothing.
Come aboard my boat. I will take you across the swamp waters.
Present this writ to your new master. They will train you in the ways of your craft.
No! Get away! Oh, wait, it's you
I'm not sending any troops into this town. There's no reason to fight these pirates until I have to.nnYour friend One-Eye should know that someday, the Pact may be forced to come back here.
I'll make a break for it while you deal with those geodes.nnIf we're both lucky, I'll meet you outside the village south of here.
The Trial of the Mind is your first challenge. The Trial is located in a hut on the northwest corner of the pyramid.
The Trial of the Mind is your first challenge. The Trial is located in a hut on the northwest corner of the pyramid.

The gerents of the vicecanons are little more than bumbling fools. But it is not our way to interfere with matters not concerning the Shadowscales.nnI am to remain here and watch. As you are not a Shadowscale, you are free to act.
I hope you made it to Stillrise and that everything is fine now.
I plan to head north, past Stormhold, perhaps into Stonefalls, but I will avoid the mire. That is west of here, before one reaches Hissmir.nnDo not tell him what I said. The letter will suffice.
The map's all yours. I should have known better. I'm no adventurer!

<<1>> didn't forget about mebut I never read the letters she spoke of. If my wife were alive, I'd ask her what became of those letters.nnNow I think it's better not to speculate. My wife is dead and that is the past.
What you've done was no easy task. We have a difficult road ahead of us.
Dendras told me about the Dominion and what you did for us.nnIt's a shame Naldyn had to die. Dendras loved him, although he wouldn't admit it.
It's heartening to see people willing to fight for us. I think the Shadowscales are heroes.
These Dominion snakes will pay for what they did to these people.
I'll pray for an answer to your voice at the shrines.nnPraying for prayers! Perhaps Vivec will appreciate how circular that is.
You mentioned J'kur. Did you see him?
Do you have the ring?
Ahh, I understand now, you will have to defeat the <<1>> to break the curse.
We did it! We walked into an inferno and emerged unscathed. We defeated a Brother of Strife!nnThis is worthy of an epic  or a monument in Mournhold!
You've done the impossible. I was wise to see the stone in your spirit.nnThen again, I'm known for being wise.
We'll hold the line here as long as we can.nnNo scamp will get past us, not as long as we draw breath.
The Altmer harms no one, but by remaining here with her, he harms us all.nnI will pray for his safety, but the wispmother must be stopped. Do what you must.
I came to this hallowed place to learn, not to deal with petty thieves.nnI'll report you to <<1>>. She won't tolerate vagabonds on this site.
<<1>> is over there by the work bench. He has a recipe for an expert ring
I fear what will happen if we do this, soldier. We'll see fire and death, but I don't see another way.nnWhen people ask you about today, tell them that Sadal did it for his people.
Well, we're one step closer to living through this day.nnI never thought I'd say that.
Who'd think a mere soldier in the standing army would be up to something like this.nnYou ever think about going into business for yourself?
Pray at the fire, soldier. You shall have the honor of ushering in the Chimer's finest hour.
Get out! Out! nnBeloved, send this lout away!
You found Risa's amulet! Please, give it to my poor mother.
I'm a bit more at peace, now that I have Risa's amulet. I feel like I can sense her presence sometimes. Like she's watching over me.
Our village is an  unusual place, traveler. You really should talk to <<1>>.
Any luck finding the crystal fragments?
You must recover the shards of my Crystal of Power.
Would you happen to have my shards?
Thank you for helping me escape.
Recover the crystals quickly before more dremora make it through!
Good luck getting those crystals.
The only way to get my crystal back is by killing those deviils. Please make sure there's no blood on the shards, though.
Strange lights emanate from three locations in the ruins above. That's where I'd look for the wards. Once they fall, the way into Vox's lair should be clear.
<<1>> has the recipe. Talk to me when you have learned it.
You should talk to my father, Grandmaster Tanval. He leads House Indoril.

I got really angry when I realized you'd preserved the <<z:1>>. Eternity is a long time, and I wanted to make that decision myself.nnBut eternity means I have forever to make the world a better place. So I guess I should thank you.
Yes?
You grace us with your presence, muthsera.nnIf this humble servant can assist you, please don't hesitate to ask.
Please don't interrupt me.
I'm happy to be out of that cage.

I follow you, my friend. I read and translate, not fight. Well, I do pirate a little bit, but no combat. nnUse the map to show the way. And quickly! The Wood Elves could be digging up our treasure as we speak!
<<1>> is down there, organizing his forces. He seems to have the situation well in hand. You should ask him if he needs you to perform any particular tasks.
Thanks for saving me!
Please! Can you get me out of here?
Hi
You'll find Noris in the army camp to the west. nnIf you end up near the weird yellow rock-trees guarded by giant lobster-bug things, you've gone too far.
I felt a burst of power from the Temple and ventured within, fearing the worst.nnBut you've prevailed. What have you discovered?
Missing Argonians and murdered Dunmer are one thing, but to have Vicecanon Hrondar missing, that's a different pot of stew. nnThe other vicecanons can't ignore this.
First, Argonians and Dunmer disappear. Now a vicecanon goes missing? nnThe other vicecanons can't ignore this.
Thanks Again.
If you banish the wisps, maybe their victims can escape.
Speak with <<1>>. She'll fill you in on the specifics. Don't waste time. The honor of the Dark Brotherhood is at stake.
<<1>> is waiting for you inside the ruins. Hurry.
Sorry, no iron to sell. At least not until the mine gets working again.
Good to see you back again, Adept. The Guild is stronger with you at our side.
I can't wait to get back to Daggerfall for a pint at the Hare and Dragon.
Well, the Lion Guard promised to let me proceed with my research at the tower, but I must wait some indefinite amount of time before Farwatch is deemed "safe."nnWhat a crock.
You won't tell anyone I tried to dig through stone, will you?
I am in your debt, stranger. nnFare you well.
I feel like someone's torn my insides out. I think I prefer the nightmares and the voices to this .nnOn second thought, no. No, I don't.
Welcome to the Anchor's Point Inn.nnYou're welcome here any time, <<1>>.
The containment cell will hold. nnWe won't be disturbed now, as we return to our primary goal of slaughtering sub-human primitives. The goblins, I mean.
Greetings, former Talisman-Bearer.nnI shall guide the new Talisman-Bearer and instruct him in the use of the wards.
I hope <<1>> is still alive. I heard horrible screams coming from the camp.
The fighting in the Worm Cult camp died down, but I'm hearing screams.
She's alive and at home, at least for now. nnAnd for now, that is all I can ask.
Go. Kill the Orc. When my digestion recovers, you will find me in Lukiul Uxith.
If you're traveling through Shadowfen, we may meet again.nnWith you, I'm sure it will always be interesting.
A new face! Wonderful! If you want access to guild rewards, please talk to the magister about joining the guild.
One-Who-Breaks-Mountains. The name is well-earned. I told Seven-Bellies you'd gone to face the Orc, but sadly, Pash-Riha has not returned.

The Three weep for the blood spilled today. I'll try to explain what happened to the house members.nnTruth to Vivec, I doubt they'll listen to me. Blood calls for blood, and this fight has been going on for a long time.
You should hurry. If you don't, there might not be any Covenant troops left to kill.
I hope Bendyn makes it back alive. He's insane, but he's a good man.
Meet me atop the cliff to the south with the totem.nnI'll turn his armor against him.
Welcome back to the Hall! Remember your comrades behind the lines next time you're on the front.
You look like you could handle yourself in a fight.nnThe Fighters Guild is always looking for more help. Talk to the Hall Steward to join up!
Don't tell me. The less I know, the better. Get to <<1>> right away and report to her. She's waiting in the center of town.
The urns of Nerathren and Faryon are in the chapel beneath this temple.nnTake some of their ashes. Then cast them into the eternal flames in the north and south towers.
I'll fight to the death to defend my home. Unfortunately for my home, I'll not be fighting for very long.
Just because you can fight doesn't mean you're invincible. Remember that.nnNot that I care. But be careful. Or not. Your choice, not mine.
Did you get the stuff from the locked chests?
Thanks for bringing back my guar!nnI can tell they're happy to be back. They're giving off their happy musk.
Please, talk to the tree-minder. If there's anything you can do to help us, the Hist will surely reward you.
Diiril was headed for those ruins on the south side of the gorge. nnNaryu and I will stay up here until the plague blows away.
The courtyard is under control, but we need to find <<1>>. Search the buildings and find where he's holed up.
Please, leave me to my grief.
Be careful of the hoarvors. They're the giant tick-like creatures burrowing through the muck.nnUsually, they're a nuisance, but lately the blood-suckers have been downright dangerous.
Seeing you in action was a privilege, friend.
The Dominion will think twice before setting foot in Shadowfen again.
You did it. And the unfortunate people of Murkwater know they've been avenged.
Use the power of the keystone well, friend.
Thank you for delivering my message to Hissmir.
These <<mz:1>> usually prey on rodents, birds, and other small animals.nnNow they're attacking us. That's proof something's wrong with the swamp.
You go on ahead. I'm going to stay here to see if I can learn anymore about the Dominion's plan for Shadowfen. Thank you for keeping the keystone out of their hands.
Welcome to the Fighters Guild. Direct all questions to Hall Steward Nardis. I just oversee the armory.
Good work. You'd fit right in with us, you know.nnDid you get the crystallized fire salts?
The Ashlanders haven't attacked again, but the job still isn't done. We need this tunnel collapsed.

I'm worried about <<1>>. Without his spiritual guidance in this time of tragedy, I fear our order will crumble.nnStill, he insists we must have the <<2>>, and he could not bear to stand away while others suffer so he remains in Muth Gnaar.
Is it done? I put the Tear of Saint Veloth in a safe place.nnNow maybe the Ashlanders will leave us alone.
It is done. These rings are bound together as a memorial to their life together.
Ah  the corruption. It's too strong.nnWho  who are you? If you're allied with the Daedra, I'll send you back to Oblivion, screaming.
I was in contemplation. It's ill-mannered to intrude. Why have you done so?
Please, leave me to my prayers. They're all I have now.
The Volek daughter can be found at the nearby inn. Look for her there.
You will find Betina hanging around the Inn. Search for her there.
My family's townhouse is nearby. Meet me there and we'll settle this.
Were you able to gather any kwama cuttle?
I'll head outside, just as soon as I staunch the bleeding.
Please don't judge House Dres by the actions of Lady Vox.nnI knew she was up to no good, but not blasphemy. Never that.
When you use the totem on Borolg, he'll think his hide is turning inside out.
Vox wasn't always like this. Once, she willingly served the Tribunal and was committed to its cause.
The stocks are south of that beached hulk called the Blasted Breton. You can't miss it.nnIn a few days, the smell will lead you there. And no taking his pants. Those are mine!
Please, they need help at the Sulfur Pools.
Thank you for helping our Glorious Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange.nnHopefully, the registrar will call soon. In the meantime, I have leads on where you can take items for trade.
The Temple of Sul sounds extraordinary. I contemplate an expedition of my own.
Are you sure you don't want another goat?
I am really not feeling well  I'm dizzy, and I keep seeing these weird visions  this has been going on for months!
Just in time! We've got a mess on our hands, worse than after a dog eats a cheese wheel.
You may look like someone I met in Stormhold, but make any sudden moves and I'll shred your false skin.
How long was <<1>> a skin-stealer? I fear it will take months to undo the damage wrought by his imposter.
Thank you for helping me. I didn't want to become snake food.nnRagara and the others are outside, if you're looking for them.
Face down in the sand isn't the way I wanted to go out. Divines bless you for saving me.
They didn't pay us enough for this job.
Do I still look poisoned? I feel different. Gods, I bet they laid eggs in my head!
You're not half-bad. Got a good sense of honor beneath that hard exterior.
Your claws are sharp, traveler. My spawn does not deserve the kindness you've visited upon his scaly hide.nnOn behalf of the rest of us, I thank you.
Great Sep, serpent of the void, spurned of the heavens, please guide your servant and his champion in all things.

You know what I'd think if someone asked me where we should look for reinforcements? Summoning the spirits of past Ordinators would have been far down my list.nnAnd how does a spirit hold a sword? Are their swords ghostly too?
Word has reached me that Zehtswater Cave is pure again. This means good things for my business.

Door's open. The Dremora didn't pull our stomachs through our nostrils. I call that success.nnThe Hist vats are further down the passage. You set them on fire. I'll stick to shadows and find signs of where <<1>> went, yes?
Ysgramor himself would be proud. Glory for the Pact!
Activate the wards while I find Tanval.
I can't face Garyn like this.
I brought this threat about. I know that now. I hope I can help stop it before it's too late.
Until the Ashlander supplies are burning, we have nothing to discuss.
Burn their supplies! Make them suffer as we have suffered.
Thank you for helping us. Make the Vereansu pay for what they did!
The sooner you talk to the Tree-Minder, the better. I'm not sure how much longer we can keep these creatures out of the village.
All's well that ends well, I always say.
We'll rebuild from this attack. Thanks to you, we can continue our holy work.
Return with the stone or die. It's really up to you, mortal.
Ready to begin your next test?
My continued presence in your realm burdens my soul. Complete your task, mortal.
This is the path you must take to bind Sadal. It's neither easy nor straightforward, rather like your mortal lives.
What a capable servant you are!nnSo many to disembowel for their intransigence. I'm practically shivering with anticipation!
Let's enter the portal. I long to be done with this.
Sovngarde awaits, my friend. I bet that Brother of Strife can't wait to go.
The death of <<1>> can't be traced to us. You don't need to know why.nnConsult the Brothers here if you need advice.
Find a way to kill <<1>> and I'll reward you handsomely.
Looking for information?
We heard a commotion outside. What happened? Did you find my father?
The Night Mother showed her favor! Your purity is without question. You shall be her vessel, her dowsing rod, to divine the blasphemer among us!
Perhaps life will return to normal now. nnNormal, what am I saying? Father's dead. Normal doesn't exist anymore.
Though I speak, do you truly listen? I suppose time will tell.
Though the Shadowscales are the leader's hands, the Speaker and the Listener are the mouth and the ears.nnApproach them with respect. Their wisdom is not for the weak-willed.
There's an aura of corruption about you.  Not of your doing, a separate danger. What do you want?
Watch yourself. This area is dangerous even when there aren't enemy soldiers prowling around.
I got word of what you did in <<1>>. Pushing back the Dominion like that. Impressive work.
You were right  about everything. My wife is as dead as she ever was. It was all simply a lie.
You are kind, stranger, though I don't know why you would do this. nnI appreciate your concern nonetheless.
Close those portals before the scamps overrun us all.
I hear you're the reason we aren't trapped here anymore. If you're ever in Kvatch, look me up. I'll cover your drinks at the arena.
There are two people trapped in the burning houses. I can feel their screams.
Hey. Hey. Thanks for saving me back in Razak's. You're one of the good ones, you know? You are.nnAnd hey! Hey. I got my leave. I'm not drunk. Just on my leave.nnShh.
Almsivi see you to your destination. With luck, the Dominion won't be so fortunate.
Mavos is about to buckle. Hurry!
My father wasn't at our camp!nnWait, where are <<1>> and the others? A tree-minder never leaves a fire untended!
I listen patiently for the worth amongst your words.
Freedom! I felt my soul being released. Divines bless you!

Veloth's hammer allows Vox to strip away the souls of those she slays and imprison them in her misty realm. They lose their memories and grant her almost divine power.nnTo challenge Vox, you need to set those souls free.
I don't understand why you're here, but there must be a reason. nnI need time. Give me time to think. Speak to my companions.
I  I have feeling in my hands again. My memories. What  what happened to me?nnThe Tribunal sent you to free me, didn't they? I knew they would not forsake me to be damned to this place.
Please hurry to Eidolon's Hollow and put a stop to Magistrix Vox's madness.
He's back unharmed! He's still a Goblin, but  well .
And Dithis has returned. Unharmed, from the looks of his green skin.
You're not with the tribe, are you? Help me!

Daedric Princes are not supposed to meddle in our affairs. My companion thought he had dealt with that threat.nnBut that is not your concern. You have done well and earned our approval. Walk in blessings.
The Hist  our link is gone!
Have you come to stop the Dominion soldier who devours my kin?
So, scavenger, have you enjoyed picking through the hamlet's bones? Have you found all the treasures you desire?
I would appreciate it if you obtained the box with great haste.
That brother-thing dead, my men safe from scamps  you've proven yourself the very soul of Ysgramor. Well done!
Being dead, I have a certain immunity to Balreth's power. nnI'm keenly interested to see what happens in the next few minutes.

In one thing, <<1>> was correct. You are no true Shadowscale. With the traitor revealed, your time here must end.nnBut I require one final service, one last judgment. You shall set my children into motion.
I'm sure that fool cat will get out again. He's just so wily.
You've done the guild a great service here today, one that will not be forgotten.
Father was such a good man. I'm glad he managed to help you.
I can't believe that Tidyn is gone.
My brother went to lead the Goblins away. We're hoping he succeeds and returns safely.nnThanks for your help, my friend.
I knew you were game.
I don't suppose the Triumvirate has smiled upon us and the Vicecanons have answered our call? I am a smith, not a diplomat or guardsmen; these intrigues and disruptions are beyond my ken.
Bakkhara thanks you again.
Thanks. We had a problem here we just couldn't handle ourselves.
I heard the alarms from the Dominion camp. Is the butcher dead?
Get going. This is no place for the living. Balreth is caged forever  thanks to you.
You can't be here for the reward. I just had it posted.
Remember, friend. Kaasha has provided. Perhaps you will not forget her.
Your skill is legendary, comrade. Stendarr truly has his arm around you. I'm glad you're on our side.
You're starting to make quite the name for yourself, you know.nnJust be sure not to be too noticeable. Aelif is worried that the brave mouse will get eaten by the hungry cat.
You'll be in good hands with Merric. he's one of our best men, and an ardent soldier against the daedra.
We must stop the daedra from invading, no matter what the means.
I'll let you search this body. I wouldn't want to disturb the crime scene.
Together, finally. S'rendarr answered my prayers.
I'd given up hope of ever being free from this place. Now I have to decide what to do with myself.
You'd be a great asset to any Ashlander tribe  if you weren't a heretic, that is.
You'll defeat <<1>>, outsider. May Sithis watch over you.
The sooner you talk to the tree-minder, the better. He's sure to know what's wrong with the swamp.
By Vivec! This is incredible.
Have you talked to Sees-All-Colors? She's right outside of Daggerfall.
This worm was a disappointment to Aelif. He was not much of a fight.
I knew Stendarr would deliver me. I knew you'd arrive in time.
I'm a very busy woman, recruit. What do you want?
I see you've found Merric.
I hope you were able to find Merric.

Your offer is most gracious.nnI think I can track her voice amongst the spirits, but I'll need the necessary components for the spell. Take this list and gather the ingredients. When you are done, use my amulet to contact me for further instruction.

Tanval left me in charge, warming the hilt until the Great Houses choose a permanent commander. Do you have any idea how many meetings I'll have to go to?nnAfter I die, I'll give Tanval a beating he won't forget.
I hope we are not too late.nnThe voice  it has faded from me. Perhaps the cries of the dead overwhelm her. Perhaps being this close to so many lost spirits deafens my ears, but we mustn't give up.
As mud is my mother! Njorlund breathes no more. Sithis has called him back to chaos.
I'm not good with talking. We should kill the Wood Elves first and ask permission later. nn<<1>> said if we did it my way, the lizards would start a riot. I've got some ideas for that, too.
When you finish, report to me or to Ordinator Eron in Mournhold.nnKill as many of the bastards as you can.
Hail, friend. I'm Saervild Steel-Wind, Warden Hrondar's deputy.
Heh, this'll be a good sale. Couldn't have done it without your help.nnI'll have to stop in to see <<1>> in Shornhelm before I cart these off to Wayrest. Pretty little number, you'd like her.
Please hurry. Alanwe's spirit is trapped.
You should leave this place before Nerien'eth senses that his magic has been broken.
You saved my life. Another moment, and I'd have been a <<mz:1>>'s snack.
I'm sorry. I didn't mean for anyone to get hurt.
<<1>> went to the Crypt of Hearts and didn't check in with me. That rogue is going to get himself turned into a wraith or worse!
Please find my sister. She has a knack for getting into trouble.
That relic you found will make our reputation. We can't thank you enough. nnEr, do you still have my control rod?
I could spend weeks taking this thing apart. nnThen it'll take Raynor years to put it back together again.
How strange to see someone out here who's not part of my tribe.
We can't thank you enough for what you've done. I hope my offering helps in your endeavors.
I don't quite know why, but I feel safer with you around.nnThank you again.
<<1>> is outside the ruins in Bogmother.nnGetting away from the Shadowscales makes sense. Assassins and murderers  that's all they are.
Give me a moment to catch my breath and I'll meet you outside.
We'll have some tales to tell in Hatching Pools. I hope we see you there.
I'll straighten out the family's affairs here in town, and then we'll see what can be done about the farm.

There's no use going back to Stormhold. I've seen their next assignment for me: a percolating mire. Sounds like a pleasant place, doesn't it?nnBy the Three, I pray giant leeches devour me. That would be a blessing.
My memories consume me.nnHow I long to return to the Hist.
We'll banish the last few Daedra once we've had time to catch our breath.
After you close these thrice-damned portals, meet me near the central dais.
I'll look for you down the river, comrade. You'll hear from us once we've decoded the journal.
Something tells me we'll see each other again. I look forward to fighting by your side once more.
It was a massacre, comrade. It was nothing like we expected.nnArkay watch over their souls.
The Cat. She held them off.
You are sun on my scales, comrade. You've returned Merric to us.
You wear the uniform of the Dark Brotherhood. Must it end this way?
You and your acts will be duly recorded in the archives. You will live on in the scrolls  forever.
There are books where we go, yes? I love the feel of paper against my skin. The raised texture of illuminated script  like a lover's lips. A lover who will never, ever nag you.
All this wailing and anguish. It sharpens no quills.
The darkness. Thank the Eye for the darkness.
This one knew Sees-All-Colors was responsible.
YOU WIN, MOTHER HUBBARD
Gimme the stuff!
You've done well. The Golden Eye has what he needs.
It's not that simple. You have to be invited. No invitation, no boat ride to the island. nnThe Academy is quite exclusive. Not like the Mages Guild.
If you want to return to Mournhold, just let me know. I exist on this plane to serve.
I've made my decision! If my father sent you to talk me out of this, you can go tell him I'm through speaking to him.
I'm sorry, I'm kind of distracted at the moment. Can I help you?
Glad to see the river has been good to you. Me? I'm going back to Black Marsh.nnI'll probably get eaten on the way there. Or trip and fall on a war. Feh.
I've always found the study of Daedra fascinating. It's unfortunate that so much knowledge about them is forbidden by the Tribunal.
You have recovered my sacred skull. Now you can restore my reliquary.
Remember, wine comes in bottles: round, thin bottles. Probably on the ground. Can't miss them.
I have to believe this is what the Hist wants. I must do my part.
I hope I come to understand why you did  what you did.
If you need a reminder, touch the vision orb again. The sequence will repeat.
Thanks again for bringing me those supplies.
All those feathers flying! Mother Morrowind, I couldn't stop laughing.
That damned <<1>> never turns his back. If he did, I'd swipe that stroreroom key from his strongbox and see what they have hidden in the storeroom!
We have a special surprise for our target in our storeroom. A very special something that will bring about a painful end. People will remember what we do, mark my word.
I think I got it from here.nnEr, thanks for the help. Maybe I'll get a chance to cast some spells after all.
Is little friend safe?
Just let me know what I can do to help.
Were you successful? Have you forged the weapon? We have more need of it now than ever, my friend. As you well saw.
We'll need time to sort this out. Sees-All-Colors wants your direct report.
May Stendarr keep you safe, comrade. We'll have need of your strength in the days to come.
You will always be welcome at the Academy. nnEspecially if we're menaced by mystic threats from beyond space and time again.
I'm glad to see you awake.
I recognize your voice. Do you hear the other voice, now?
Pain opens the door to corruption, separating body and spirit. nnHealing cannot be complete while the corruptor lurks nearby.
You have slain the rot at my roots. You have restored my clarity.
Welcome. Today, you've protected those who cannot protect themselves.
They didn't expect to see a Dunmer, so I made sure they didn't. I can be stealthy at need.
My brother-in-law is in danger. He's a strange one, but he's family. Please help us.
You should talk to the boss lady. She'll want to debrief you.
Thank you for driving off the Dominion. I found <<1>> now I just have to convince him to come home.
The damned dryskins will pay for what they've done!nnSomeday, we'll take the fight to their own homes.
Jofnir murdered! The whole guild will hear of this. And Aelif's suspicions.
<<1>> was an excellent master general. He deserved the honor of death on the battlefield.
Thank Stendarr. Guildmates! Ready your blades for battle.
By the Twin Ravens, I owe you my thanks, mortal.
By my sacred oath, that is the only portion of the performance I am allowed to impart. Seek more knowledge in the mora, where the bittergreen grows thick among the bal.
I can say no more. Seek further knowledge at a cornerclub, and while you're at it, have a mazte for me.
More I cannot say. Seek in the tallest of the bal, where the roobrush and chokeweed grow thickest.
Go carefully, comrade. Uncertain times in Tamriel. Only thing you can be sure of is a good weapon.
I must finish this performance. Please wait.
You always help yourself to bags that don't belong to you?
Look! See! Didn't mention this before, but you have beautiful eyes.nnWhen you die, can I eat them? Snack?
I'd keep my snout shut about the Vicecanons while you're here. They aren't exactly well-liked - in fact some of the boys would love to show them their gizzards.
Pardon me. I must begin this translation. These runes  fascinating.
Curse the Mad God. I don't know what game he's playing with you. nnBut I do know the stakes.
That was unexpectedly competent. You'd make an adequate house servant.nnI don't suppose you'd consider it? The pay is meager, but the fringe benefits are appalling.
Puppy-killer! Come to steal me books? Wha ? Who? Where? What? When? Sometimes why!nnSpeak up! Honesty is the best policy, as far as you know.
My task at court is distributing the flesh of the fallen to the citizens of Crow's Wood.nnYou are a citizen now. Would you like eyeballs? Tender spleens?
The toll! Paid the toll! Featherless has paid the toll.
Take care of your new vassals, fledgling.
I can't face my partner just yet.nnLet me be for now. Let me be.
Who are you and what do you want with me?
Surii finally sent help? The Goblins went crazy and started killing without warning. I barely escaped!
There's grub grass under the western waterfall.nnYou'll need to stuff it in a vial and rush it back here. No time to lose on this brew!
That mammoth won't shut up.
What were we talking about? Please, Mistress. Don't hurt me.
Greetings.
Greetings.
Who? What are you? Another phantom come to take me to Sovngarde?
I know you  I have heard of you at the Sanctuary.
I see you've accepted Svari's invitation. She will be a worthy successor to Tirora. One more step in rebuilding what was destroyed.
Alas, the evil giant Sinmur has returned. Every leaf trembles now. Tell Vigrod everything you saw.
Do you still have business at the prison?
You have my precious crystals! I can smell them. Gimme!
Slay Cloggg and earn my esteem. Oh, and a reward.
Why am I still crying? These are tears of joy.
I'm glad to see you're still alive. Have you found the shards of the Crystal of Power yet?
Have you found the crystals?
Shoo! On with it.
Go away, before I call a guard to deal with you.
<cough> Do you have the crystals?
You saved our lives, but to what end? Our homes are destroyed and Sinmur could come back at any time.
I couldn't bear the thought of leaving my wife for Shor. Thank you.
I'll be honest. I thought I was dead. Thank you, for all you've done.
I can't belive this. Shor's Stone ruined and the Companions' Hall overrun!
I can still smell the blood. It was all over the mine and those foul Reachmen. My mining days are over.
Wish I could've taken a blade to those Quagmire bastards myself.
You'll find <<1>> in the main building. He's seen great things concerning you!
Oh, you're not a Goblin. nnIf I had a weapon, I would have flattened all these stinking runts, but they caught me by surprise. I told Surii this was a bad idea!
Thanks for the assist thanks.
I'll make a break for it while you're freeing my guards from those Black Soul Gems.nnIf we're both lucky, I'll meet you on top of that hill to the south.
Are we far enough away from those cultists now? I'd rather not run any more, if it's all the same to you.
I shiver to think what those Supernal Dreamers hay have done to me.
I doubt <<1>> took <<A:2>> far from here.
Come, come! Let's find Nord. He hides in building next door.
Thanks again for freeing me.nnNow, you should go off and have more adventures. I think I've had my fill of those.
It's good to be free.
You look familiar. Are you?
<<1>> and I are going to rest before we brave the road to Mud Tree.nnMaybe you should rest, too. You don't look so well.
Hey, here comes my hero!
Well, this is different. I guess.
Maybe next time, I can fight at your side instead of watching from a distance.nnI'd like that.
Prepare yourself for trouble. The lamias will slay you for their supper, if given a chance.
I'm glad Shalidor found you. I need your help.
Who are you? Did Surii send you to kill me?
We'll keep the Dominion trapped in the ruins while you seek <<1>>. And watch out for the lamias! They're territorial and vicious.
