I feel a little pity for the prisoners here but without the keystones, I don't know that we can defeat the Dominion.
What do you need? It's not like we aren't busy enough.
Praise the maker! You saved her! As her life is saved, so is mine!
Fallowstone Hall has fallen! There's no hope without the Companions!
I knew she was alive, and I knew you were the one to save her! I'm eternally grateful!
<This Nord was recently and violently killed. His belongings are in disarray.>

Many thanks for for your help but the mine isn't quite up to full production again. It's getting organized again and all, but my shift hasn't gotten back into the mine yet.nnSo, I was wondering if you could help me. Again. As it were.
Find more of whatever that is and take it to Garm.
Thanks, friend. Be careful on the roads. The Maulborn are everywhere. If you see one, stab the s'wit or run away. Don't try to talk to these fanatics. You'll get nowhere.
I figured <<1>> would send someone after the totem. Just had to hide nearby and wait for rescue.nnAnd here you are. I'm not delirious enough to think she sent you to save me.
What are the Maulborn up to? Why experiment with a plague? It doesn't make sense.
Welcome to Vernim Wood. Dark waters run in this river.
I can feel this body decaying. So much pain. Please, kill me!
A still-beating heart. Either Dajaheel sent you or this is an extraordinary coincidence.nnMay I?
Be safe in your travels, and may Tall Papa guide your steps.
Shall we raise the curtain? Begin the first act?
Magnificent! That couldn't have gone better!
Be careful. The blood has called in a pride of sabre cats. They're prowling on the ridge north of the farm.
You were able to light the fires! This is great news! I could see the glow from here! The Commander has returned, you should talk to her and let her know of your success!
My friend! I didn't think I'd see you again so soon. Look, I need to see to this wound. I know I can trust you.nnWill you go after my girls?
Shor's favor! A friendly face. I managed to get away from the Worm Cult  and now I'm trapped up here!nnCan you clear a path for me?
Shor's bones!
We're lucky to have you.
If you would like to join the Mages Guild, please visit the closest guild hall.
It seemed urgent. Please don't keep her waiting.
It seemed urgent. Please don't keep her waiting.
Thank you for choosing me. I am here to serve my Prince.
I've nothing left, so these will help a lot. After I've mourned my husband, I'll sell them and use the money to leave this place. It holds too many bad memories.
I hope you can help Yiri. Her father saved my life when we were children.
A slave in such finery? Purloined, no doubt! Grovel suitably for your crimes and I may behead you apace.
We owe you our lives. If ever you travel this way again once we've rebuilt it, you will be an honored guest.
<Gugnar is dead.>
If you gather the <<1>> for the tree-minder's ritual, she'll help <<2>>.

I erect the spine of welcome to you traveller and crave your ear. My clutch-brothers and I came to this village seeking our brother, <<1>>, hoping to remove him from this terrible place. But we are too late.

I erect the spine of welcome to you traveller and crave your ear. My clutch-brothers and I came to this village seeking our brother, <<1>>, hoping to remove him from this terrible place. But we are too late.

I erect the spine of welcome to you traveller and crave your ear. My clutch-brothers and I came to this village seeking our brother, <<1>>, hoping to remove him from this terrible place. But we are too late.
I have been waiting for our brother's return. He is somewhere among the Goblins.nnMay he find good mud and plentiful fish.
This foreman will not admit defeat. She's like the iron she mines.nnOf course, that doesn't make her wise.
Collect <<1>>, <<2>>, and <<3>> to make healing poultices for the wounded farmhands.
Always sad to see a good man die. Leo's death, just now? Hilarious! Hah.
Bastards just won't lie down and die. Well. I'll see to it we give as good as we get. Ysgramor!
Don't wait for me. I'll be along shortly.nnI have some supplies to scrounge up: shovels, food, that sort of stuff. The life of a quartermaster is an exciting one.
You should see this if time of day is noon
The bodies of my egg-siblings were desecrated by <<A:1>>! Until they're whole, I cannot return them to the Hist.
Fools! If they knew what I knew, they would be praising me instead!
I can show you where Merric is. Follow me.
Evacuate, they said.nnI'm going to lie here and look at the sky for a while. I think if I stood up, I'd fall down.
Ysgramor must be watching over you, friend. You shouldn't be alive.
Get that fire lit. We'll be ready to go when you get back.
We can take care of ourselves from here. May you swim freely down the river of life.
I wouldn't have thought those milk drinkers would leave their cozy taverns to come down here.nnI'll have to get this wound seen to, then. I'm going to need my sword arm!
You're alive! I didn't think it possible!
You need three runestones to unlock the door. Move, you pustulant maggot!
You. Get me out of here.
I've got nothin' more to say to you.
I don't understand why he'd trick us. We followed him here, like lambs to the slaughter.
We knew a man, Old Rory. He went in. When the soldiers dragged him out, he was missing all his bones.nnI'll give you until my fire burns out. Then I'm coming in after you.
<The skeleton stands mute before you. It sways slightly with unnatural life, but shows no sign of malicious will.>
You still here?
This won't take long. Patience, friend.
Be on your guard. I fear the undead will hinder you as they did me. Don't let them prevent you from summoning the spirit.
You're not one of the bandits. Help me!
Fetch water she says she ALWAYS says fetch water it's like thats all I do. Oh, sorry hello there.
Mmm is that a pail of water? I am so parched.
Please, look for my family. I miss my dear Rexus!nnAnd Geilund, of course.
I never thought I'd be glad to smell that dog's rotten breath again. Thank Kyne!nnSomeone's getting a big steak for dinner. Yes, he is!
Thank you for coming along when you did. Squeak!nnEr, excuse me.
You were ordered to leave. What lies beyond this door is not for your eyes.
Go away, little squirrel. Before the shiny stones find you.
Wish me luck, my friend. I'll need it, this time around.
Don't worry, adept. I'll be fine soon enough. Now that you've restored my mind, I just need some rest.
<<<1>> bounces back and forth under your hand. He looks like he wants you to follow.>
Good, you made it.
So, what did you find out?
Welcome to trouble. Our little Captain Rana doesn't know what she's doing.
Thanks for your aid. That was like being touched by Sheogorath.
I'll never look at a cat the same way again.
The mad god Sheogorath can't resist meddling with mortals, eh? His disciples all belong in a cell.
Right, that's done. But there are three other fields around town. You'd best make sure they're all doused.
There are three other fields in town. Could you make sure the fires are out in all of them? I'm going to Last Rest Barrow.nnWhere's Trynhild? Why wasn't she here to help me?
That's one less worry.nnThere are three other fields around Bleakrock. Make sure the fires are out in all of them, then meet us at Last Rest Barrow.
Why did they do this? The whole farm smells like murder. Like bacon.nnI'm going to meet my family at Last Rest Barrow. Could you make sure the fires are out at the three other fields around town?
You should go on inside the barrow. Rana was looking for you.

Flesh-walkers rarely visit our dreams, small one. The whorls of your thoughts bring warmth to our own.nnSoon we awaken, to nourish ourselves back to health. You must leave, or be dashed against our dreams.
I have the spell prepared. Are you ready to receive it?
Ah, it's so good to meet someone with the right priorities.
The traitor has fled from justice. Right into the arms of her supposed foe, Molag Bal. nnHow deep does her treachery go? We must follow her to Oblivion itself!

The messenger found you?  I'm glad.  I was hoping that we'd meet under better circumstances .nnThis is a sad day for the guild, but I'm glad we'll at least perform this terrible duty together. I still can't believe Sees-All-Colors betrayed us.
That statue, those nests  are we within the Hist's memories? And those creatures  brothers to this Hist!nnSomething's wrong. The Hist-brothers seem agitated about these memories.
I have lived to see one of the worst calamities in history ravage our realm. It must be stopped, no matter the cost.
I can't thank you enough for finding my brother.
Find the Earth-Turners. I'm going to sit here and let the fire warm my bones. nnMaybe I'll take a few more of them with me before I go.
I'm off to celebrate. Stay moist, friend.
They  came from underground! I saw them drag the others away.
Greetings, friend. What can I do for you?
Were you with the Vicecanon? Is the Egg intact?
Find Damar. He can tell you more about what's happening here. I'm not from this village. I know nothing other than what I see.
Why should we run? Can't we fight them?nnWhy is everyone so worried? We are Nords and they aren't.
Geting out while the getting's good, eh?nnI'm not arguing. Just wish Maesa would put down her tools and join us. My wife's stubbornshe'll be the last to go.
If we actually evacuate, I can down tools and leave in seconds. No reason to stop working now.nnSo. There anything you need?
I don't understand any of this. We haven't evacuated since Captain Rana came. Is this some kind of practice evacuation?
Ain't leaving our pigs. No chance. Them damned Daggers would carve them up for bacon.
Don't know why I'm still here. Just spreading the kindling for the damn Daggers.
I'm sure we'll see each other again, friend.
Alms for the homeless?
Close the portals around <<1>> before the Covenant can get a foothold!
My guar were lost, and now they're found. Thank you, sun on my scales.
We must evacuate. We'll make our way to Davon's Watch.nnIt's always the same. When the waves of war roll in, the people of the earth are lost to the flood.
You are the sun on my scales. I will think of you every day at evening meditation.
We're safe from the Daggers, but we're still in danger. nnIt's always this way when war looms.
I will offer myself to the Pact army. The Daggers will regret leaving <<1>> alive.
Another book and more waiting around.
Confront her, my friend. Perhaps the life of Sees-All-Colors might yet be spared.
What are you waiting for, comrade? Kill her!
Good choice!
Good.
Good choice!

I still live! The Countess spoke of my service as a punishment  but truly I am happy just to laze in the river's waters. Merric will make an excellent Guildmaster.nnAnd I have you to thank for this. My friend.
It's really quite an amazing gift.
Why are you still here? I asked you to leave! What do you want from me?
If you see <<1>>, tell him to watch himself.
Just because a man has a ruby doesn't mean he's desirable.
I know it's a hard choice, but you must go to the fort or the docks. nnLend your strength where you think it's needed most.
Like I'd ever want anything that belonged to that peasant.
No one will miss him.
I'll just go away. I was a fool to think mortals would feel the way I do.nnLeave this place, and don't return.
Challenge some of our conscripts. Get them to spar with you. Anything you can teach them will help.
I think it would be best if we left here as soon as we could. I don't want her coming back and deciding we can't leave.nnThank you for everything, friend. We'll be gone as soon as possible.
We should've sent you to Black Marsh. You weren't meant to be a slave, <<1>>, my son.
<<1>>, I've seen you talking to my daughter without bowing your head. Never do that again!
<<1>>! I heard you talking to <<2>>.nnYou're not going to Percolating Mire, are you?
Quickly! Before they kill more of my kin.
Hurry to the docks. Seyne won't last long by herself.
Captain Rana wouldn't let us follow her. She made us turn back. nnShe blames herself for Bleakrock. She's not out to stop the Covenant. She's out for redemption.
My new mead really knocked you on your arse! I call that an unqualified success!
Welcome to Dhalmora, little egg.
I'm not sure what to do now. Should we rebuild or should we leave Lower Yorgrim to the giants? I'm just not sure.
I can't wait to tell Haraldar that this Kazok bastard is dead.
The people of Lower Yorgrim will soon come around to my way of thinking. After all, we are what we eat!
Did you give Skorvild the meat? What happened?
What can I do for you?
Give me a few minutes to catch my breath. Head into the keep. I'll join you in a few minutes.
Careful. It isn't safe here.
I saw Skorvild's militia headed for the manor house. What happened up there?
Now the time of our triumph is at hand!
You're the sun on my scales, comrade. You've returned Merric to us.
Please do hurry. She said it was important.
Why are you interrupting? Aelif is speaking with a guildmate.
It's good to see some people have open minds. nnI hope to see you again, friend.
It was a massacre, comrade. It was nothing like we expected.nnMay Arkay watch over their souls.
I can show you where Merric is. Follow me.
Please do hurry. She said it was important.
Kyne bless you, stranger.nnCaptain Alhana commands the brigade. She's an excellent leader and a terror with a blade, but they should have been back by now.
Thank Stendarr. Guildmates, ready your blades for battle.
Find a way to kill <<1>> and I'll reward you handsomely.
I think my Inga would be pleased that her family name and business will go on. And we're making some damned fine mead, if I do say so myself.

We're in the dark stuck in this cabin. We need to know what's going on out there. Eliminate witches and the enthralled soldiers and search them for anything that might prove useful.nnIf you can find the Keepers, we might just have a chance.
Why are you interrupting? Aelif is speaking with a guildmate.
Inga would be so happy to see the meadery open again.
I'm glad someone warned Davon's Watch. I just hope it was soon enough.
Pardon me. I must begin this translation. These runes  fascinating.
Pardon me. I must begin this translation. These runes  fascinating.
You're back! Were you able to kill any of those beasts? And did you bring us any of their pelts?
I'm done with Lower Yorgrim. Things were starting to get bad there even before the giants showed up.
I smell fresh Kyne's Breath! It reminds me of when I was a little girl, running through the fields in spring.nnI miss those simpler days.
Before we continue, we need to be at our full strength.nnI need you to get those sprigs of Kyne's Breath back to Fresgil at the other cabin. Once Droi is cured, we can worry about our next move.
End the witch. For all of us.nnDon't worry about me. I'll be fine. This tree's doing a great job of holding me up.
Leave me alone. Just when I thought I'd drunk away all the pain, you tell me about my mother. Looks like I'll need another pint now  maybe four.
I mourn the loss of my brother. I have no time for strangers.
Kyne forgave us both this day. We need to repent. But to be in Kyne's favor again! I forgot what that felt like.
I knew Stendarr would deliver me. I knew you'd arrive in time.
We must press on. We'll burn these foul eggs after you clear out the spiders.
I'm sure you have more important things to do than chat with me, comrade.
Please, just leave me alone.
Get to the watchtower as soon as you can. nnThere's just no time.
Everywhere you go, the Daggers roll back like an ebbing tide.nnStill, there are plenty more. The Pact will need a steady supply of guar-hide armor.
Vivec keep us! The Covenant is raiding along the coast.nnI have family in Senie. I wonder if I'll ever see my brother again.
It will take time to clean up the mess the Dominion dryskins made of our homes.
I can't believe I missed the whole battle with the Daggers.nnWho am I supposed to fight now? Dark Elf nobles? They can't fight for bull stool, and when you hit them, all they do is whine.
You upheld my honor and the honor of Windhelm. This Ebonheart Pact is worth more than I hoped.nnMay all your enemies fall before you!
Do as I say. Leave this place.nnYou can't rescue the Keepers. They don't need to be rescued, since they no longer exist.
When my spirits are low, I come to this place and bask in its healing waters.
She's alive  hurt and frightened, but alive.
Were the rumors true? Was it a necromancer after all?
The finest plate in Stonefalls, straight from my father's forge.nnYou've never seen the like. I guarantee it.
I'll listen to Bishalus next time. I've got nothing to prove to her.
Please. Don't let Darj down, not after all he's done for us.
Speak to <<1>> in the keep.
Speak to <<1>> in the keep. Better be quick about it.
Go to the soldiers in the Keeper's house. I'm sure they're confused and uncertain about events here.
Thane Mera needs to speak with you. You can find her in front of the palace.
Go. I'll meet you on the docks.

I expect you've come to learn the secrets of the great mages.nnThere's ultimately one secret, young woman. Do not compromise. If you believe something is true, you must require the Mundus to act in accordance with your will.
I have no desire to speak with you ever again. Be gone.
I appreciate the mild entertainment you've provided.nnThe best thing about your time here: no mess to tidy up. So far.
I appreciate the mild entertainment you've provided.nnThe best thing about your time here: no mess to tidy up. So far.
Now that you've given me back my life, I have much to think about.nnMaybe I'll take some time to rest before I put together another expedition. The Fighters Guild is in your debt, my friend.
War rages in Cyrodiil. We need people like you in the fight.
Why are you talking to me? You have your instructions.
I said I don't want to discuss it.
Have you finally brought my Crystals back?
Good luck freeing our soldiers. I'll meet you and the soldiers at the barracks when you're finished.
Good luck freeing our soldiers. I'll stay here and wait for the detachment from Windhelm to arrive.
The War is that way soldier. There's nothing more I can teach you.
You have demonstrated valor today. Thank you. Please let Thane Mera know what happened and that everything is fine. nnI need to consider my brother's plans and how to best counter them.
I need to go. I need to get out of here. Those things are everywhere!nnPlease, my friend may still be alive. If you see her, you need to save her.
You must light those watchfires.
Well, I have to say, I'm rather shocked you actually completed the contract with all your bumbling. I don't know what the Night Mother sees in you, but mine is but to obey.
Don't touch me. You stink of life.
Get going. Holgunn is a veteran and a decorated officer. He'll know how to handle the Daggers.
Back already? Did you see King Jorunn?
Finally!  Someone of my stature being held like a dog preposterous.
No! Keep him away from me!
The spirits of the tombs watch over you, my friend.

Well, well, will miracles never cease. By the panic going on around here, I suspect you were successful. Don't get cocky, get off this boat as they'll be looking for who was responsible. Meet me back at Sanctuary.
Digging away! Puffy little cheeks. What have you found?

And, there you have it, our little oaf may have what it takes to be a productive member of the Brotherhood. With enough hard work and dedication, you may be able to elevate yourself above dead weight. Hey, don't knock it, it's more than I expected!
You! You saved King Jorunn! You certainly know how to make an impression!
Thank you for coming along when you did. Squeak!nnEr, excuse me.
You've done it! The immortal story of the Silvenar and the Green Lady has been put right again!nnBut tell me, who corrupted Indraseth in the first place? Did you find out?
Our <<1>> is useless! It holds none of the magic it once had, and it's all <<2>>'s fault.nnWhat's going to happen to the Silvenar and the Green Lady if the story's changed?
Though I wish you could stay to drive out the remaining Houndsmen, I'm sure you're needed elsewhere.nnGood luck on your journey.
<Some of the wounds on the corpse came from weapons, but others have clearly been inflicted by animals.>
Welcome back, champion! What news do you bring from the peaks of lonely Skuldafn?
Any luck acquiring some of that Voljar mead?
Head for Skuldafn as soon as you can.
You have to get past the Worm Cult. Spinner Indinael needs help!
Someone found help. I feared it would soon be too late.
They've taken her inside, haven't they? Are we too late?
<The giant stares at you expectantly.>
So much death .
You there? Can you help me?
You're not one of them. Please, you must help me!
Well? Is it done?
Let's get this done. I'm eager to crack some heads with you.
You're right. You've been right about everything. These horrific events must pay forward to a better future.nnIf not for my daughter, then for all the daughters and sons of others like me.
My head aches and everything looks blurry.
Why would anyone attack Cragwallow?
Everyone seems confused. Did you find out anything at all?
Oh Gods, it's you they're looking for! They'll kill us all!
Save our soldiers, please. We must stop all this senseless death.
Are you another creature come to torment me? I've had enough of this maze!nnSpeak, apparition!
He's gone. I can feel it. His presence faded when you struck him down.nnBut so is dear Rala. I shouldn't have sent her. She wasn't ready.
Mother Mara, why can't I hear you? Why can I not feel your warmth and love?nnIs this place truly so bereft of all hope?
Who do you think you are, taking my energy?nnYou think defeating me once will be enough to enslave my spirit? I'll see your bones sink into the tar first!
Thanks, whoever you are.nnBut why did you do that?
<A few bloodstains mark the surface of the stone table, but there is no sign of Spinner Indinael's body, and no hint of her spirit.>

I hope Kireth knows what she's doing. Can we even read Dwemer maps? I guess we'll find out soon enough.nnHmm. If I shine a light through the orb, we might be able to see the maps on a nearby rock or wall! Pardon me, I just had the most amazing idea.

I hope Valeric didn't convince you to join our cause. Our battles never end well. True, his father's a bastard, but he's a strong bastard. Valeric can't beat him and those who help us usually die. nnBut enough depressing talk! How can Jaruk help you?

The Hound came, seeking solace for his broken heart. The others turned him away when they heard what he wanted. A memory. A chance.nnI couldn't. His tale tore at me, and I wove a bit of him into the story. But soon, he became the story.

Stormfist scouts hide in the trees. They ambush us when we least expect it. The giant can help you knock the cowards from their perches. Then kill them and collect any orders they carry.nnIf you find something, meet me at the camp to the west.
Do you fear it, avatar of the Silvenar? Feel its hunger within your bones?
The giant near the natural wall, just behind me to the west, is ready to help you. Just give him a poke and he'll do the rest.nnWe'll launch our attack once you're inside and we hear the signal.
<<1>>'s fate is in your hands.
Thank you again for freeing me from those roots. I don't think I can ever look at vegetables the same way.
I'm lucky to be alive, I guess. But I don't feel lucky. Just sad.
I want to catch whoever's responsible for this.
Do you have my lord's gems? Is looting the dead so difficult?
You got the key? Open the cage!
Any luck finding my sword and shield?
You defeated him. I didn't think it was possible.

I've failed my duties as a spinner. The story comes first, above all emotion. Above all pity. I pitied the Hound, but it was a trap.nnAnd now, the Silvenar and the Green Lady will always have, and always should, join as one.

Here is where the Green Lady practiced archery. She practiced with her friend Unthor and her cousin Borodor, but she outstripped them from the very first day. It was then that her aunt, the Green Lady Finoriell, began to take notice of her potential.

This is going to be great! Raynor will sulk for a bit, but what else is new? Soon he'll be inventing something amazing to use in the next ruin! nnAnyway, thanks for your help. And feel free to use the lift over there when you're ready to leave.
My mouth is watering just thinking about a nice juicy bear steak
The altars are cleansed! My brothers and sisters will rest again!
You can get into the storeroom now.
Well, you did find a cute little goat for the main course.

You have been a boon to us. We Keepers would have failed our people if it weren't for you.nnWe'll have to continue to refine Rilis' prison, but even the Daedra should have trouble breaking him free from four binding stones.
Shor's, Boulderfall. Hard fighting on familiar ground. I have family here in the Rift, did I ever mention? Just hope they're staying safe.
The altars are cleansed and the Worm Cult's resolve is shaken.
So much death.
Poor, misguided Valeric. I wonder what weakness drove him to this terrible end? I shall grieve for him. In my own way.
Not now  sleeping .
Has the friend of the Silvenar found the distasteful bits? Only then will the path be clear for our friend.
Something you need?
The Commander and I were able to fight our way back to the Tower with the wounded, and now we can regroup.
Your story has many more chapters. Go, live them!
Don't worry. I'm not really sick. At least, I'm not too sick.
Speak with Jadvar, inside the cave. But don't get your hopes up.nnIf the Three Old Gods require your help, that's between you, them, and the Ternion elders.
You're still alive, congratulations. We may have a chance to repel these invaders after all.
My power is returning. We must press onwards.
Imiril will live. Go. We need you to handle Rilis.

By Aetherius, we barely managed to contain that lunatic!nnVoranil might be right. If these binding stones don't hold, we may need to take drastic action to defeat Rilis. Even if it means making a Daedric pact.

You come to support the slumbering king? When last I saw him, his skin was pale and his breathing shallow. His life force slowly drains away.nnIt would take a miracle, or a favor from the Three Old Gods, to save him now.
You seen them strange folk coming and going in the cave cross the way?
The pirates know something is up. Won't be long before they start looking for us.nnI think the captain's on the other side of the ship. If we can take her out, the rest will probably give up. I hope.
Y'ffre, Z'en, Auri-El, I beg for mercy! I repent!nnYou're not one of those Steel Shrikes, are you? Can you understand me?
The patrols led me in circles. It was a complete waste of time. Have you found anything?
Ready to leave when you are.
Yes! So that's how they do it. A portal. How elegant!nnI was hoping they turned into bugs, though. That would have been much more spectacular.
The promise of battle holds no fear for me.
Don't you have a dagger to bloody? Now move along.
Back already? How're the other stormwardens? I can hardly wait to give those Sea Vipers a good thrashing.
You've seen something about where my niece came from. I fear her path may be turning.
The Dreamwalker's work has begun.nnIf you wish to observe his progress, pray to our totem spirits. If the Three Old Gods hear you, they will show you images of the Dreamstride.
The family  <<1>>. They need help. Please!
Thank you for saving the Silvenar! I can't believe we all got out alive.nnAlmost all. If only Raen could have been with us .
I thank you for doing what I could not. You saved the Silvenar and protected him from mercenaries and traitors.nnI will do my best to keep him alive on our road ahead.
Go, please. Help her. Save who you can!

My wife Jakild and I share the cabin farthest to the north. My brother Kerthor, we don't talk much. He keeps to himself in the cabin near the wayshrine. And my cousin Agnedir lives in the cabin near the springs.
Thank you for helping us. I don't know what I'm going to tell Agnedir's sister.
You've returned. The moons surely follow your path!nnDare I hope my fellows-in-arms are free?
I should have done something as soon as I saw that helmet. Now my family has paid the price.
Bah, cultists! They are unworthy foes for Ysgramor's Companions. Thankfully, they are your vermin to kill.
Thanks for getting me out of that tight spot. The Green Hunters were looking a little hungry, and I'd no interest to see what they'd eat next.
Jakild and I are lucky you came along when you did, friend. Once the draugr settle down, we'll get back to work on Bonestrewn Crest.
Brilliantly done. Your waters flow swiftly now, touching many shores.
Please, let our people pass to Sovngarde. They  they must be in so much pain.
You need to get into the mine and shut down whatever they're doing in there. And I need to get out of here.
Vigrod finally set me loose on these fiends! We must not give one inch of ground!
You beat me. I lose to my cursed brother. Again. Perhaps he is the better ruler.nnRegardless, in front of my ancestors and my sister, I am undone. Do what you will with me.
Magicka binds my spirit to this place. I can't even see my captors.nnLocate the ambassadors who survived the attack. They can help you find me.
At the peak of Skuldafn, upon this holy dragonshrine, the Ebonheart Pact is sealed.nnGo, find my son. Let him know that my brother is dead and that we are victorious.
You've returned. This imprisonment is no longer bearable. You must free me!
You don't look like one of those tree-cutter Sea Vipers. I'll assume that means you can be trusted.nnIs Mariel safe? Is help coming?
Azara was always more interested in exploration than research. She loved breaking into an undiscovered ruin and gathering all the objects she could cart away. I'm going to miss her.
Silvenar is to the north, past Valeguard. The preparations for the handfast are being made, so I can stay here for a little while and recover my strength.nnI'll be safe enough.
Charadin might still be alive. Oh, why did I run and leave him?
They were still in Mauloch's shrine when I ran away. I think <<1>> was stabbed by the shaman!nnHave mercy, Z'en! Don't let us be parted like this!
King Jorunn is up ahead. Hurry! He needs your help.
Move quickly, or you'll be trapped. The storm waits for neither man or mer.nnAn army waits outside. Be ready.
You're back! Did you save the rotmeth?
The traveler departed, ever in search of answers, on a path toward greatness.
I suspect I'll live, though perhaps with permanent, debilitating injuries, confining me to crutches for life.
It's so good to see my sister again. I promise I won't be long, but I need to speak to her. nnGo. I will meet you after and we'll stop my brother!

This fiend Thallik Wormfatherhe cannot be allowed to hold Wuuthrad! We will get it back. The king's soldier, Captain Hrosta, searches for Wormfather even now. nnIn the meantime, you must stop the Daedra coming from Coldharbour.
Hakra said Wuuthrad shattered when you defeated Thallik Wormfather.nnAh, do not blame yourself. You fought with the courage of Ysgramor.
You're not as clever as you think, mortal. I will kill you!
Majorn waits for you in the nearby manor. He'll be pleased by your willingness to engage in a proper conversation.

This disaster drew me away from the brewery at a critical stage. I've got to get back. I mean, obviously, I don't fear harvesting the thunderbugs and their maggots at all. Not at all. But I've got to get back. You understand.
You think you're so clever, mortal. Remember this: I will kill you!
Alchemy. It's not for the faint of heart.
That was exciting!
When this trooper is patched up, I'll move on to the next. You'd better get going.
My friend, we've come a long way from <<1>>. You've known me now in two lives. It's only right you're here as I begin a third when I bond with the Green Lady.nnNow, please, enjoy the celebration.
The chamber is right through there, past the barricade. Just be careful of the trolls.
Quiet! The Houndsmen are in the ravine below. I'm here to make certain they don't come up and attack the Silvenar's camp.
You found straw on that thing? We have a lot of farms around here. But  best place to find straw in Riften is at Guridda's stables. Head out the southeast gate, and go left. Can't miss it.
You found straw on that thing? We have a lot of farms around here. But  best place to find straw in Riften is at Guridda's stables. Head out the southeast gate, and go left. Can't miss it.

That thing was carrying pig iron? Strange. I wonder if that was old Gomund.nnThere's only one place in Riften to get pig iron - the Scorched Hammer smithy. It's near the center of town, west of the market square.
With your help, I know we can succeed.
Please, don't kill me! You don't understand!
Thank you. I could see no future for Silvenar as long as I was imprisoned there. But the Hound's bonds are broken, now!nnQuickly, you must continue your mission.
You can find Commander Yjarnn on the bridge in the middle of town.nnGood luck getting any information out of him, though. He won't tell his own troops anything, I doubt he'll tell a stranger.
We will be leaving shortly. Trust me, we will never forget how you saved us.nnMay our paths cross again someday.
Freedom exists, as do I, in any state. But my brethren, you must unlock their bonds, one way or another.
I don't understand. None of the refugees will answer my questions. It's like they're hiding something.
Please, apologize on my behalf about the delay. We've had a lot of trouble around here lately.
Please, we need help. Things are bad here.

Look for Thod over near the tents. Maybe someone in the camp knows where he disappeared to. The skeever's late and I'm tired.nnIf you find him, send him back here to report to me or Guard Hloenor over there.
Please, find Sal. I don't want to die with his blood on my hands.

All of Silvenar celebrates the handfast, and you should, too. I see your life's paths open before you  your tale does not end here, but continues further on.nnKnow that the Bosmer will always be grateful.
Get moving. Those boats won't spontaneously combust on their own.
I love a good party!
I can't believe this happened. Why would someone want to attack a company of royal workers?
What foul Maormer trick is this? Another attempt to loosen my tongue?
A zombie carrying rotten fish? Hst. Fish don't rot in water. Not like that, at least. It must have gotten it from the docks to the west.nnUgh. That smell will be in here for weeks.
You're heading to Nimalten? Luck on the road, my new friend.
Oh, if you're still looking for Thod, I wouldn't worry about it. He and the Commander headed for the barracks. Thod's getting an earful, I'm sure.nnI apologize if we wasted your time.
You do a great service for Rigurt. Rigurt knew he could count on you!
I'll get the mead to Windhelm as soon as possible.
You'll never find those clothes without me. I've hidden them too well.

Do whatever it takes to make the Argonians and Dark Elves happy. We need to get them back here before more people start dying.nnI won't allow the Prince's ignorance and ill-founded opinions to lead to the dissolution of the Pact.
Thank you again, friend. But good-bye now. Rigurt has much to do, much to do.
Please hurry. Arithiel saved us. We can't let the Worm Cult kill her.
Pay attention and speak to <<1>>.
I'll set the few troops I have to search out any remaining cultists. If any of those Worms remain behind, we'll find them.
I hope the Silvenar survives the handfast bonding. I know he has great spiritual reserves, but .nnWell, anyway, I'm certain he can handle the celebrations!
I knew you were a hero! The spinners told us everything! nnThe celebration's being prepared!
What happened in there?
That poor man! Such a terrible thing.
How dare you judge us? We do what we must to survive!
Sweet Tree-Minder. Sinmur is a monster that must be put down.
I'm sorry, I need to watch the road for Worm Cultists. <<1>> can answer your questions.nnAnd thank you for stopping. We don't get many visitors.
I'm sure the king will be well pleased to see you again.
His majesty will be pleased to see you again, I'm sure.
If you stay here, the Worm Cult will see us. Go chat with the chieftain Suhlak if you're looking for conversation.nnDo me a favor? When you leave, don't step on any twigs.
Well met, friend. Do you bring news?
They want me dead? Let them come. I welcome another chance to prove myself. Fjora bends knee to no man!
Well. This can't possibly go wrong, can it?
Tell Hallfrida not to worry. We'll be back on the walls in a few minutes. Go on, now. I've got to organize this mob.
You're supposed to be in the .nnWait, who're you?
Rescue those captives. Once they're free, head up to the arena and see <<1>> for your debut.
Thanks for helping us. Fildgor's lackeys won't catch us off-guard again.
Be quiet. I don't want them to notice us.
Ah, the murderer's accomplice. I think I'll kill you first.
My wife Asgi is in the mine. I wish I could go help her.

I'm getting tired of being treated like second-class citizens.nnThe Nords have turned their backs on my people more times than I can count. It would serve them right if we refuse our aid when they call upon it.

When you get inside the courtyard, you're going to need to find a key to get into the Jarl's manor.nnDon't worry about me. I'll catch up with you soon enough. Just be careful in there, all right? Dhalen is dangerous.
I don't mind hard work, but I hate when someone holds a knife to my sister's throat.
Sorry if I was rude. I'm just trying to protect myself and my husband.
The bad Nords are gone now and Hjolard is very happy!
I spoke to my wife. She's a spitfire, let me tell you. She said hello, gave me a hug, and went right back to work.
If Fildgor sends more troops, we'll be ready for them.
Did you hear that? I think the Worm Cult are crawling around on the roof!
We'll do what we must, with no help from you. Dog of the Jarls!
You still here? Are you bothering Hallfrida? What do the Jarls want with my granddaughter?
Oh! Good to see you. I have sad news: Golun is dead. We heard the sounds of a struggle. My soldiers and I arrived too late.
There will be more murders before this is done. I can't put my finger on it, I don't know how I know, but I do. And I grow restless sitting here, unable to act.
Please, we can't keep the King waiting.
I only received my promotion a few weeks ago. First time commanding in the field, yeah? Can't believe it kicked off with  this.
Thanks to you, the hengekeeper made it through. But I thought I'd be able to speak to the matrons if they woke .nnIs the same force preventing me from rooting in Treehenge thwarting me now?

The High Kinlord's power has grown terrifying.nnI don't know that we can stop him, though we must. Tamriel is in grave danger if Rilis reaches the surface. Even if we catch him, we'll need to devise a stronger prison than the last one .
Head south from here. Once you run out of good, dry land go a bit further and you'll hit Stormhold.nnLocate Vicecanon Hrondar there; he'll direct you.
You're going to the bandits to get back my silk? So Turil did hire them! I knew it, I knew it!
My silk. Did you find my silk?
I am so relieved. Holguss is fine. He came out, wolfed down some stew and went back to work.
I never saw the Orcthane's followers move so fast! They ran out of here, crying like little babies!
I knew those big goons were nothing but cowards! Now we can get back to work. And for real, this time.
I need help. Things haven't been normal for a long time.
We won't be caught off guard again. We'll protect the King.
Jorunn can't die. The Pact won't hold together without him. May the Tribunal help us all.
There is sorrow here today, but the Companions will recover. And I will remember all of it.
I'll get everyone together and head back in a group. We'll be right behind you.
I'll explain later. We must wake the matrons as soon as possible.
Thanks to your actions here and at Cradlecrush, we should have things back in order very soon.
Greetings, stranger. It looks like you have something for me.
You've done the guild a great service here today, one that will not be forgotten.
Danus may seem paranoid, even irrational at times, but we owe him our lives.
You're starting to make quite the name for yourself, you know.nnJust be sure not to be too noticeable. Aelif is worried that the brave mouse will get eaten by the hungry cat.
You're starting to make quite the name for yourself, you know.nnJust be sure not to be too noticeable. Aelif is worried that the brave mouse will get eaten by the hungry cat.
Your skill is legendary, comrade. Stendarr truly has his arm around you. I'm glad you're on our side.
Please find my friends. I keep thinking about all the awful things that might have happened to them.
I just want to sleep for several days after this ordeal. I think <<1>> wants to talk to you though.
The door to the storage area is inside the shed. Sorry. Careful not to burn your hands on the door.nnWe'll try to get the flames out while you're in there.
If you've got questions, now's the time to ask while I prepare the ritual. It works differently for two people.
When you poked your head into that tent, I thought I was going mad. What are the odds we'd meet again here, of all places?nnIn case I haven't said it enough already: thank you.
When I saw you on the road, I said to myself "Raynor, your friend is here to save the day again." And you did!
My friend. I'm glad to see you again. We could have used you  wait, those papers. You have some of the delver's notes!
What? Must be a delusion. Nobody down here. I'm not dead yet, Shor!
Strangers. Intruders. All the same. You distract us from our duties.nnBegone, before the ritual is disturbed further!
I see no malice within you. Is there compassion in its place, I wonder?nnDo you seek to purge the poison within the henge?
No time for pilgrims! We must attend to the departed Green Lady.
What's going on? I feel so strange .
Will you come to Boulderfall's aid?
I'm not in this line of work to make friends. You can run along now to wherever you were going before we met.
Ghorgarz stands victorious!nnNow, Ghorgarz, you face a true challenge: <<1>>, son of our esteemed ally, <<2>>!
Were you and Merric successful?
Please, my liege-lord. Make haste for Honrich Tower. Whatever darkness grows there must be stopped.
Please hurry. My shipmates may not survive interrogation.
I hear you're helping Danus secure the camp. Many thanks.

We're in your debt. If you ever have need of blades, come speak to me. I guess I should find some more flowery, Thane-like speech, but that's not how grandfather raised me. Speak plain and honest, he said.
The first thing we do is ensure the dead have been given the Rites of Arkay. We'll have to send to Riften for a priest. I'm not going to let another damned necromancer play around here.

We'll hunt Thorulf. You live with a man for a decade, he gives up some secrets. I know places to look for him.nnIf we find him, I'll contact you. I can't think of a better mate to have at my side for that fight.
I was told I might find you here. I have an urgent message for you from <<1>>.
Please, hurry. Being trapped here is nothing like resting in the mires of Ouze.
Learn what you can from Sinmur's song. Just know, the skalds may not recognize you for who you are. Some of the dreamers aren't as aware as I.
Are you ready to go back?
We'll need time to sort this out. Sees-All-Colors wants your direct report.
Get outside and help Sjarakki. I'll keep an eye on Thorulf.
I'm going back to the fishing village. The other survivors need my help, and I must make amends for the acts of my brother.
This seed existed before the Green Pact, before the Bosmer learned to calm their forms. Before the Green Lady and the Silvenar.nnIt will heal <<1>>. Take it to her before she dissipates.
We're lucky to have you.
Another book, and more waiting around.
Good choice!
I'll set to work deciphering the Mad Lord's gibberish immediately. I'll contact you as soon as I know something.
Why are you still here? I asked you to leave! What do you want from me?
Just because a man has a ruby doesn't mean he's desirable.
The Circle of Iron links me to this world. As long as it exists, I can torment you stupid mortals!
If you see <<1>>, tell him to watch himself.
Like I'd ever want anything that belonged to that peasant.
She's waiting for you at the Riften Guildhall in The Rift. Good luck, comrade.
No one will miss him.
Please, father. I've told you all I can. Don't take my sweeties again!
Don't worry, Jarl. I'll keep an eye on these bastards. Even if it means my death. For the Pact!
I hope you like the tune. Remember to listen closely, let the melody flow over you.
See if you can make sense of that absurd book.
Why are you bothering me? And how did you get in here?nnMy guards have apparently gotten lax in their duties again.
Ha! Once the Stormfists knew we had weapons and weren't going to back down, they remembered they had an important engagement somewhere else.
Silly old woman. Don't think I know my tales. Just wait, I'll be the greatest bard the holds have ever seen!
Nimalten reminds me of Bleakrock. All these good people, oblivious to danger. If only we could have protected my daughter.nnHave you learned anything?
Get out of here, I'm busy.
There was a scream and the sound of fighting. When we arrived, Golun was dead. It happened so fast.
We must defeat <<1>> and the Worm Cult once and for all. Are you ready?
The Reach are here too. I need to see what they're doing. These aren't the same as the ones in Shor's Stone, so who knows what horrors await?
Get the <<mz:1>> from the camps. Their distinct glow gives them away.
She's preparing a ritual space at the Evermore Guildhall in Bangkorai. I'll see you there, Adept. We're so close!
Good luck at Virak. Break a few Covenant heads for me, will you?
The Maormer will interrogate the crew, and their methods are very unpleasant!
Speak to <<1>>. We haven't much time.
You performed a great service for the dead. Thank you.nnI look forward to hearing your tales in the halls of Sovngarde one day.
Show it to the Khajiit bard over there. She's been pestering us for written words, and we've finally got some!
Fools! If they knew what I knew, they would be praising me instead!
Now that was a fight for the bards to sing about! nnAnd to be honored by Ysgramor himself  this was a good day, my friend. Yes indeed.
A blight has been cleansed from Tamriel today. My heart is flooded with pride, and my mind is soothed like calm waters after a storm.nnIt was an honor fighting at your side.

Your heroics today have even succeeded in impressing me, and that is no small thing.nnThallik Wormfather and the ghost giant Sinmur are both dead. Mark my wordsthis will be what King Jorunn's reign will be remembered for.
Ha! I told you I wouldn't turn into a zombie. Though I've had the strangest craving for that Akavirian meal with the raw fish.
We must not forget the names of our valiant fallen.
Thank you for collecting the amulets. Narir will get them to our soldiers' families.
I've arrived. And I brought my fellow mages with me.
Careful. It isn't safe here.
I mourn the loss of my brother. I've no time for strangers.
<Lieutenant Ehran is dead.>
Velyn Harbor is safe, the townsfolk praise your name, and you've shown our captain's true colors.nnA busy day for you, eh?
It's really quite an amazing gift.

The poison weakens the King. We need a substance to bolster his life force.nnThe Ternion monks also require a focus. An object or even a person. Something or someone that possesses a rare power can serve this function.
Good.
<The woman's glassy eyes stare fixedly at the rough dirt path.>
Don't worry. I'll fight when it's time.
Let me get myself together. I'm all right. I'll be all right.
I hear much merrymaking. Perhaps that secret ingredient is good for more than a severe hangover.
I can't believe it! I'm going to lose everything!
Give me a moment; I'll head to the bridge. That's where the lieutenant will be, right?
It brings me sorrow to see creations of nature brought so low.
Rotmeth requires a certain tang from the thunderbugs, and their maggots are essential in eliminating the more dangerous poisons.nnFortunately, they're plentiful around Cold Cave.
There's no time!
You really are a wonder, aren't you? If I were younger, I might ask you to show me how you do it.nnThat's not the life for me, though. Not now, anyway.
This is our town! They've stolen our goods. Burned our homes. Threatened our families! We must rid Velyn Harbor of the invaders! To me!nnMore showed up than I expected, thanks to you.
You're probably best equipped to handle something like this.nnWe're always up for an out and out brawl, but coshing someone on the back of the head's just not right.
The Voljar family has always been known for its exceptional mead. I need to carry on their legacy.
<<1>> hopes you'll consider what you've witnessed here today. There are lessons to be learned, and perhaps choices to be made.
Please. If the Stormfists find the Sigil, they could undo generations of good will.
Sister-of-Wind will recover. Breathing normal, body healing. Her dreams were tainted by the injuries.nnAlways happy when I help another. Always remember the ones I couldn't save.
My mother said I would bear the Sigil one day. That's why I left. nnI guess it's true what they say, though. You can't escape your destiny.
It's nice to see another strong guild member around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that.
We can't let the Daedric Anchors remain here, comrade. Duty calls.
We have our fair share of problems with the undead around here. You may have noticed.
It's shocking. <<1>> was an excellent master general. nnHe deserved the honor of death on the battlefield.
How dare you help the Argonians. The filthy lizards! They killed my wife!nnShe put her faith in the Dreamwalker. Put her life in his hands .
Grida is too serious. Kind of like you. If you find her, great. If not, whatever. Don't worry about it.
You go away now. Laughs gives you nothing!
I'm alive. It's a miracle.nnI saw Stormy-Eyes in my dreams. He guided me through the darkness. He helped me find my inner strength.
This is our pool and you're not invited.
Go. Save the King. We'll track Fildgor down and wait for you to return.
Now! We just need to find Viveka and get her back to town. And I can forget about these gods-cursed mountains.
I'll be fine here for a bit. Need to get my strength back. Go on. Maybe I'll see you when you come back this way.
<<<1>> died of exposure to the elements.>
I can't wait for the chance to present this to the council. With Andewen, of course.nnValaste and I will have much to discuss.
Without your help, the tale of Andewen in Ezduiin would have gone very differently, I think.nnGood luck in your travels.
<<1>> has taken you into her story. I think this means that you're telling the story with her, through your words and actions.nnHow exciting!
I'm feeling a bit nervous after my brush with death. I bet I'd have been a lot more nervous in an urn, though.
Jiluza is thankful to be out under the open sky.
Ah, smell that fresh air. I think from now on, I'll stick to the nice safe translation work. nnField work is for senior researchers.
I've already written home to my parents. I'm not quitting! I just need a short break.
I hope Telenger has noted my bravery here. Something good must come of this!
I did my best! I don't care what you say!
Good try. Not enough to beat me, but good try.

Steady-Hand swears he's the best hunter in Eastmarch. Says he can nab more rabbits in a minute than anyone else.nnI've got an idea, if you don't mind bending the rules a bit. Come back and talk to me after you equip the hunting bow.
Thank you  The Maormer won't make it to Vulkhel Guard thanks to you .
Next time you find yourself in Vulkhel Guard, drinks are on me!
A good sense of discretion goes hand-in-hand with a talent for self-preservation. You've done me a favor here, but don't push your luck.
You should have seen the look on Steady-Hand's face! He deserved it. Especially after what he said about your mother! It's not true, is it? Nah, no one would do that.
You returned! And you have them! Even after all these years, they're still beautiful. Their lovely smiles. The energy flowing through them.nnIt's like we were never apart.
We'll recover from all this. At least I hope we will.
The next time our ocean-faring cousins pay us a visit, we won't be unprepared. Many thanks for all your help.
Keep an eye out. Something big's about to happen on Auridon
The Maormer will think twice before threatening Vulkhel Guard again!
Your look is grim, friend. So they had been turned?
Well, that could have gone better. Maybe it's all that royal "we" nonsense. nn"We call upon our ancestors." It's all rather condescending, isn't it?
I'll get these to the Artificer. I'm certain he'll know what to do. The dead of Ezduiin will finally know rest.
Dajaheel and the Centurion Gjakil are in charge, back at the camp. Speak to the Argonian if you want to pitch in.
My portion of the ritual is complete. Now I must pray for the restless souls of my ancestors.
While many of the spirits linger, they will slowly dissipate. It will take awhile for the reality to sink in.
That was a good fight!
A harrowing confrontation. But at last, this ordeal is ended.
I swear, it's like being home for New Life Festival. The family's been drinking since noon, and everyone wants you dead.
You! What are you doing here?
Where  where did you come from?
I'm yours to command.
Kill the wizard!
Always the last to reach the checkpoints. Always off, foraging for squirrels, or birds, or what-have-you.nn<<1>> has some explaining to do.
Please do all you can for <<1>>. She must've been caught by the Cult.
My gods, it worked! You've destroyed the stone!
<Golun was stabbed repeatedly until he died. A faintly glowing object is scarcely visible beneath him, as though he'd tried to hide it.>
Stay close. If we stay together, we might survive this.
Dajaheel's at the main camp, just outside the treeline. She'll set you aright. Good luck.
Dajaheel's at the main camp, just outside the treeline. She'll get you set.
<<1>> and his guards have already entered the ruins. You'll need either the shards or comrades to survive in there.
We'll hold the door, but you need to clear the Reachmen out of the Hall.
Get into the Hall! We'll protect the entrance, but you must dislodge the Reachmen inside!
Stars keep you. I think Cannie will be all right.
Thank you again. We'll be ready to retake the town soon.
Telenger didn't say anything, but I can tell. He's disappointed. I'm going to spend the entire trip home asking the Stars how to get back into his good graces.
Auri-El watches over us, through you. Thank you.
I don't know how Svari can stand it. Hard to focus.
The High King has been asking about you. About time, my friend.
Aargh!
You've got questions, I can tell. Ask away. I'll tell you what I know.nnThere's a lot of werewolves to fight. And <<c:1>>'s waiting.
My friend, I'm glad you're here. My confrontation nears. Your presence bolsters my courage and gives me hope.
Ah! It's almost over.
It does me good to see that thing dead. And Saromir's free at last too. My poor, dear friend.
<<1>> must answer for his crimes.
The Canonreeve  betrayed us.  Betrayed us all .
Blood for the Pact! If we had an army of folk like you, the Daggers wouldn't have dared to attack Stonefalls.
Defend me!
To think, all of our research  ruined! It's all those savage cultists' fault!
Wasteful practice. Abhorrent! Oh, pardon. I did not see you arrive.nnAre you another pilgrim to Treehenge? Be wary of the cultists. There is no telling when they may strike.
Most of the villagers are here in the market square, but some may be up in their homes. Vadda'ra thanks you for sharing this burden with him.
Whose body was this? The flesh reeks. You placed me in one of those Cultists, damn you!
The Silvenar needs help if we're ever going to get to this wedding.
One of the others said you lifted the curse? Amazing. Not sure I should trust that kind of talk.
(You open Tildur's stash and find it filled with contraband goods: Daedric artifacts, skooma, and daril.)
Rid Auridon of that murderous scum, even if you have to burn my lighthouse to the ground.
Don't worry about me. I'll make it out of here alive. See? My wound's stopped bleeding finally.
Thank you for turning in that smuggler scum.
I heard about what you did on the docks. Thank you. I'd gut every Worm Cultist in Skyrim, if I could. But I need to take care of my niece first.
We're excited, but we're still arguing! The sooner we get our songs down, the better.
Shadows and blood, don't leave me like this! Don't let them get away with this mockery!
You'd never know my drum's been battered about by Houndsmen, would you?
You've saved us again! We'll never repay you at this rate.

Thank you for our lives, but what is life without fame? I mean, music! We need our instruments if we're going to be the stars of the ceremonies!nnWell, along with the Silvenar and the Green Lady, of course.
You're not one of my men. What are you doing here?
Without your help, the giants would still be bearing down on us right now. Good work with that necromancer.
Maybe today is a good day to die!
You're the Queen's new favorite, yes? I recall you from Vulkhel Guard.nnGood that you're here, I suppose. She'll need the help.
Good luck in Mathiisen. That town forges some of the best steel in the Isles. We can't have traitors in the middle of that operation.

Good luck in there. nnLike I said, Captain Landare will be able to tell you more. She'll be manning the cordon at the edge of town.
Thank you so much. I could never have done that by myself. Raynor's sleeping right now, but when he wakes up, I'm going to tell him how great his device worked.
Succeed where I failed.
You're not one of the regulars here at the Flagon.
<He stares icily at you.>

Be wary, vestige. Our very plane of existence is in peril. The threat of Molag Bal looms across all Tamriel, and chaos spreads in its shadow. nnDanger roams the land and will assume many forms. Do not let it catch you off-guard.
That descendant of mine headed to the summit, straight into Drodda's murderous arms. I'm sure he's finethe Direfrosts are an able-bodied lot.nnBut he may need a little help.

You make a mockery of my game, mortal. By all calculations, the mages should be dead by now. But no. They still live.nnI must say, however, that my game hasn't been this exciting in a long time. So I grant you the ultimate boon. The right to choose!
A new face! That's a rare occurrence. Welcome to the Everfull Flagon, friend!
Leave me be, stranger. I'm a very busy man.
Well. This is going to set back the order for Firsthold. The High Kinsmen will not be happy.nnMaybe I can supplement the order with some product from Greenwater.
I. I didn't know they were with the Heritance! nnI support the Queen. Some of my best friends are Khajiit!
Have you been up by Ezduin? I was working with that Telenger fellow as one of his students. nnI had to leave. That mage is unstable, if you ask me. Not worth the trouble.
Are you a marine? You know you have to tell me if you're an official.
Shouldn't you be in the forge, cat? I'm surprised they let you out. It's not break time. nnOh. You don't work here, do you? Well, you should. Only thing your kind's good for.
First Silsailen, now here! Is anyplace in Auridon safe?
Get out of town while you can. I am.
I've only been here a week. Had to leave Phaer, leave everything behind. A plague swept through, you know?nnFigure I'll make some money, send it home to Hendil. Maybe he can buy supplies.
Bad enough I'm stuck on this garden of an island. But working alongside Khajiit? nnTerrible. Mangy, rotten creatures. I bet their meat tastes as bad as they smell.
Work is work, I say. There isn't much of it in Deepwoods. Just hoping I can save some money to send back home to my family.
I just finished a stint at the College of Aldmeri Propriety. Awful place, but I got through it. nnFigured I'd see the rest of the island before I go back to Eldenroot.
So much death. But perhaps, now, Mathiisen will see a brighter day.
Zurka thinks she will be leaving soon. Auridon has proven a bit too  exciting for the likes of her.
Banished to Oblivion and the man still won't acknowledge me.nnWho are you?

We're off to search the second wreck. I'd be obliged if you could follow Jalan's wake and see what's keeping him. Bring him along to the other wreck, so's I can dress him down for being a lazy lackwit. nnIf he ain't dead, that is.
What you got there, stranger?
Curse the Daedra. Damn them to drown in the Font of Harmony.
The Eight watch over my poor father.
That Admiral spook, Sithis sink him, seems to control all the skeletons.
Go on, mate. nnIf things go well, I hope to help you when you face the Admiral.
We've got you covered. Dragonguard! Hold the line!
Stop standing here and get the Amulet!
Sing a song of glory for us when you get back home, eh?
These Daedra can't possibly win! I'm too good looking to lose!
<This Altmer is dead. He was badly beaten before his death.>
I pray that this curse will soon be lifted.
Do you have it?
Good choice, mate, giving me the crown. nnNow I think I'd best be introducing me crew to their new captain.
My cousin wrote to me about what happened at the Serk. You did a good thing there.
My father just kissed me on the cheek and ran out. What happened?
Fish, fish, fish. Little fish in the basket, little fish in the stew. Little fish in the cookpot, I love you.
So many little treasures. A shell, a coin, an amulet. Akkuz finds them all.
Mother says working with your hands is for Bosmer. Stuff that. Anything worth doing is worth doing yourself.
Trade feeds Vulkhel Guard like rain feeds a tree. There's almost as many crates here as there are raindrops in a storm.
Rough ride coming in. Mathad will spend this evening thanking Jode and Jone. They allowed us this passage.
Last time I ride that kind of storm. Damnit, Y'ffre. Why do you have to go and be like that?
Yes? Hmm. I don't recognize you. nnPlease go. My wines are available only by appointment.
Move on. Get inside.
Welcome to Vulkhel Guard. What can this one procure for you?
I think I saw a ship on the horizon. Didn't catch the flag. But I'd swear the colors were Maormer. nnBut they couldn't. Nah.
Welcome back, my friend. Did you find it? Was I right? Was the source of power I sensed one of the fabled Lights of Meridia?
Our house destroyed, our village in ruins. At least I still have my Pirtar.
What a mess. What a mess! I can't imagine what my mother will say when she hears about this.
I'm not sure how, but you did it. Thank you.
It's a good thing you came along when you did. Just when I thought things couldn't get any worse. But you managed to pull us through.
So much water here. So different than this one's homeland. It is beautiful, yes? But also so. Wet.
Sorry, have to have the place looking right. <<1>> wants everything just so for the Queen's visit.
Looking to buy, sell, and trade? You've come to the right place. What do you have in your pack there?
We just got in a shipment of steins from the Woodhearth. Primitive art is so in fashion these days.
You call that bag adequate? I don't call that adequate. Here, let me sell you something before we both get embarrassed.
Was it Glow Dust and Snowberries? Or Glow Dust and Hanging Moss? Oh, apologies. What can I get you?
I sense life. Magicka. Ah, a customer. The best kind of life! What do you need?
So much to do. Please, speak with the Mistress if you're looking to sell.
The Stars welcome you, traveler. Take a moment to look over my arms. I assure youthey are as deadly as they are beautiful.
You are needing a good meal, yes? Everything I serve is sugar-sweet and ready to eat!
I don't recall seeing you around here before. Hmph. You hardly look like club material. Best begone, commoner scum. We're dangerous men!
Mara's Heart, your gear has seen wear. Perhaps a new helm?
I heard Almion was coming to check on me when he died. This is all my fault.
So many of the Marines made it back. Thanks to you.
Have you figured out the sequence?
You look familiar. Were we flirting just a little while ago?
Hail, hero! The King recovers after the attempt on his life. He will see no visitors.
Please, go. I  I want to be alone with the dead right now.
You ever try making a bow out of bones and rocks? Trust meit's about as fun as it sounds. Thank Auri-El someone's out there gathering lumber.
We are all in your debt, friend. The King needs to rest right now.
I brew fragrant elixirs and delicate blends. What can I get you?
You're going into battle wearing that? Hmph. I know we can do better.
I used to sing for thanes and kings. I danced around and had many fine things.nnHow about that! I made a rhyme. I've still got it!
Tell me you're here to buy. Stars know we've got the goods.
If you're working in cloth or leather, I'm your man. What can I get you?
You're here to work metal, yeah? Check my wares before you get your hands dirty. You'll find something worth buying, I guarantee it.
Go with the Tribunal's blessing, in the name of the Lord, Mother, and Wizard.
I knew you would make the right decision. I just hope the three of us are equal to the task that's still ahead of us.
What a cruel game we were forced to play! This one is just grateful that we all survived.
Can't talk. Have to watch the Defender's mutt. Last time I make jokes about a cat owning a dog.
If I wasn't so drunk, this would probably hurt a lot more.
This one tends the grounds. Tries to ignore what the Altmer say. Their words hurt Razigad, like lashes of a whip.
What'll you have?
Hey there! I'llI'll have another.
What could you possibly want?
Stars, make it quick. I'm waiting for someone.
Don't  Don't I know you?
Yes, lowborn? What can I do for you?

If they make you choose a side, you should consider the tree. Er, Pesty. Estre? Yes, that's it.nnShe keeps her troops happy, no matter what. A strong morale will win this battle. That, and I feel no pain. Now that's an advantage! Drink!
Find the broken mask I seek, or your outlook is bleak.nnRemember my clues, for they'll lead you true without lies or ruse.
I said go away and let me read my book in peace.
No harm shall come to Juline while she is sworn to me.
What is that? Is it the end of the world? Arkay's beard!
So. How did it go?
Ah, the brave hero who broke the spell that bound us! So good to see you again, my friend.
The Mages, they are kind to this one. Even say one day Taranza could become Mage. If she rakes hard enough.
Go on. I won't live much longer now.
Look at this, dear! The Temple to the gods in Vulkhel Guard. One of the most beautiful spots in all of lovely Auridon. And Xarxes himself seems to be keeping the image from my mind.
Think of the power I could give you if you were to side with me.nnOr you could choose another and feel the wrath of the very power of which I speak.
What  what happened? Ugh, my head.
Go, go!nnDo what you need to so you can make your decision. There's killing to be done still and the Shadow Court can only amuse us for so long.
What? Like Jilarga doesn't have enough to do everyday. No time for stupid questions.
A muffled voice cries out: nn"It's locked and I'm tied up. Please, get the key from my father."
Where's Marq? Did he listen to you?
We came to Velyn Harbor for aid after the Crimson Raiders destroyed my village . It doesn't look like the town is in a much better position than we were. I hate irony.
The cursed shard has been destroyed. Currents of happiness and grief flow through the river this day.
Hhmph. No lavender. Last time I trust that Greenvine liar. Sorry. What can I get you?
The best goods, straight to you from Grahtwood. Hand-hewn by craftsmen at one with the Green.
Who? Go away.
Please forgive me for saying so, but your raiment is ever so  mundane. Why not explore some enchantments?
Stars guide you, traveler. Robes for the discerning spellcaster, right here. With the Brothers in Arms.
Hah! Best armor in Auridon, from the Brothers in Arms. Get it fresh from the forge!
Brothers in Arms armor. You need new leathers? I'm your man.
Why are you so interested in the casks of mead? You should leave them alone.
What? Is it the height? Or that I'm a woman? Either way, stop staring and tell me what you need.
You remind Tuzil of his son's cub. So full of life. This old cat's just good for asking things like 'What can he get you?'
These records are in complete disarray. It's enough to drive a Proctor insane.nnUntil the Dominion sends more troops, I'll be here attempting to restore a basic semblance of order.
Brews are always better with meat! But I know, I know. It's an acquired taste.
It's not a party until someone gets eaten! Ha! I'm just yanking your vines. Probably.nnSo. Who's hungry?
Welcome. Shall I attend to your account?
And fair day to you. Your account?
This is my beach. Mine! All the treasure here belongs to me!
Diamonds? Rubies? Ziss on them! Nothing but polished rocks.  My soul gems are the only stones you'll ever need.
We all have burdens to carry. Why not take on a little bit more, friend?
This one sells the best blades in Tamriel! No jokes, no substitutions, no refunds, just high quality steel. At an affordable price!
Please. No more. I can't take any more .
Ugh, these sweaty workers. Always getting damp on my chairs.nnYou look the respectable sort, though. Get you something?
Stars watch your steps, traveler. As they watch over Telenger!
Oh, thank you so much. I knew Mister Nurin was all right. nnThank you for saving him. Thank you. Thank you.
I always knew Rosalie had something like this in her. She has a crazy streak a mile wide.nnIf William's back, maybe I'll go back to the farm after all.
This place is a mess.
My father is upstairs. That so-called Thane attacked him.  He's all right, but he wanted to speak with you.
I'm not sure what's worse. Nightmares about Daedra, or the months of cleaning and rebuilding we have ahead of ourselves.
The house is a mess. Almost wish the fire took it completely. Probably be easier just to build a new one.
We're five and three-times blessed to have you here.nnThe loss of so many Marines. Hard to bear. But at least we can bury the dead as victors.
Be quick with your discussions. My patience lessens by the moment.
By the Hist, I'll be more careful next time. If you're ever in Duskwallow Hamlet, my nest is yours!
Father. Why?
Another fragment of my soul lies to the south. It's heavily guarded, so be wary.nnI would not fault you for turning back. It only gets tougher from here.
Did <<1>> send you? What's he want now? Shall I strip naked and chase thunderbugs?
Have you spoken to <<1>>?
Amazing to see that old thing in action. To think our ancestors were so clever.
Rulanir didn't deserve that. No one does.
We may be stuck in Coldharbour, but Nelhilda forgave me and we have our souls back! Sovngarde is ours again, when the time finally comes. nnI will never forget what you did for us. Thank you.
Thank you for freeing me. For freeing Faindor.nnOur tormentors washed him in fire during the day, and he slept only to face the same all over again. I hope that he can rest easy, now.

You've done the impossible! I've seen those Daedric fiends flay the souls of my friends with but a word. Your power must be immense. Dwarfed only by your generosity.nnI  the shards have merged and my soul is whole, once more.
We're back, thanks to you. Let's see the Vanguard try to kick us out again!

Ah, the prodigal soul has come. Are you really prepared for this?nnIt's a pity, I admit. You could have been more useful, but the Master was very insistent. I actually almost liked you after that bit in the Warehouse.
You're through. Are you going to let me go?
Damned pirates. Think they can take the Prowler away from me? I'll show them what <<1>> looks like from the yardarm.
<The lieutenant is unconscious.>
I can't tell you how relieved I am to learn you recaptured the lighthouse.nnWe've had enough trouble around here already.
When I went to bed last night, I dreamed of a fully laden ship docking in the harbor. I thought it was a good omen.nnCouldn't have been more wrong.
This makes little sense. How could pirates capture the largest port on the Long Coast without a fight?
No time for talk! Go deal with those dungheaps!
I'd like to know why <<1>> pulled her Jade Dragoons from <<2>>. Their absence nearly led to the Jackdaws' success.
You're very kind. I'm sorry to make you go to all this trouble. I feel like such a fool. nnI don't have much, but I'll pay you what I can.
Thank you for returning my <<1>>. I thought she might make for the boat after she ran away.nnYou've saved me quite a bit of trouble, friend. What can I give you in return?
It is time to leave. We will follow you.
Our stronghold is under attack! The bandits can't enter the longhouse. It would be a massacre.
So, have you decided to help me? My clan can be a powerful ally if you let us.
Stay back! I'll cut you! I really will!nnIt's the voices. They make me crazy. Always whispering to me  saying strange things. The voices .
I hope my first mate didn't get herself captured. nnShe's the best I've ever had. If she doesn't come back soon, I'm going after her.
Thank you for rescuing my employees! When all this is over, stop by my tavern. I think you'll like it there.nnI'll head back to Haven right after the cat-lord frees it!
With all the excitement of the pirate attack, it seems the Dominion is less interested in the business of a humble innkeeper and his loyal staff.nnBut best not to mention it.
What are you standing around here for? Get moving!
We've got this covered, get down there!
Welcome, bloodkin.
Go find this thing for me.
Hey you, I need some help.

Pirates routed, delivery made, and you of all people to do it! Strange times, my friend.nnI think I'll stretch my legs before heading back to the Prowler. The rest of the crew can handle repairs, for once!
If you can see this, you can pass the "And Step" case.  Are you ready to end this test?
What do we have here?

There are many objects of Divine origin scattered throughout Tamriel with which one might recharge something as powerful as the Amulet of Kings. The difficulty is determining which is the safest and most logical to utilize.
Is my playing disturbing you? I am sorry. I find that music is the balm of the soul. It has always brought me peace.
Yeah? If you got nothin' to say, then leave me be.
Hey! Good to see you.
Don't worry, as long as we're here, the Prophet won't be unguarded.
Hello. Don't mind me.
Oh? Greetings. Sorry. I was just thinking.
You heard the prisoner! Head to the entrance and warn the guards!
Do be careful out there. These books are harmless enough, but they aren't the only things flitting about in the dark.
Have you found the weapons yet?
You! Have you come to help me?
Stranger.
Thanks again, friend. Can't wait to reinvest my winnings in a new racer!
My career as a researcher may not be dead after all.nnMight even get a promotion. You've saved me from a life in the glass mines, my friend. May the Empyrean Light protect you, wherever you go.
Please, please! Just don't hurt him!
Good luck. As if you'll need it with my Snooks in the lane!
Go! Confront them. Fight! Win!
Thank you again. Look at Leggy go!
They were good little rabbits. Kind and brave. Thank you so much for your promise.
You are urgently needed at Eidolon's Hollow. With my blessing, you can face Vox and survive.
Hopefully we can find Ari  Arianas before she causes any real trouble.
If you reduce Vox's forces and manage to survive, be sure to report back to <<1>> in the camp outside or to <<2>> in Mournhold.nnYou'll be rewarded for your assistance.
If you can see this, you can pass the "And Step" case. If you checked the Quest Journal, Tracker, and logging out, then you're ready to finish the quest!
I heard what you did to the Sentinels. Their egos will be bruised for weeks! Good job.
Any Worm Cultist out to defile our shrine gets a mouthful of arrows. Give a whistle if you see them headed this way.
Yes? What is it now?
So. We should probably get this over with.nnYou lead the way.
First chance I've had to catch my breath. You're welcome to any food, bloodkith.
Oh, thank the Eight and whoever else is listening! You're not one of those Red Rook thugs.nnAt least, I don't think you're a thug.
Ah, you're the one. Seems we need to have a chat about <<1>>.
I'll just stay down here for now. It's peaceful. Maybe I'll open a bottle of Len's vintage wine while I wait for the trouble to all go away.
I'd love to chat more, but I really must finish this report. My fellows in <<Ac:1>> Mages Guild are chomping at the bit to learn more of our findings!
I refuse to do a lick of work for these Red Rook hooligans.
I am ashamed to say I'd almost given up. But you helped me find my courage.
Oh, don't be cross. You'll find your friend, or you'll die trying. Either way, you won't have to worry about it for much longer.nnMortals are so finicky.
<This statue of a male Elf is significantly less worn than the others.>
Hello.nnYou aren't an illusion, are you?
Enough. I yield, I yield!
Maybe I am cut out for the <<1>> Guard. Patience and vigilance are the same whether you're fishing or on watch. Not one pirate made it past me!
Woe be to <<1>>! Pact-soldier dooms her to rot in a cell, away from the warm sun!nnIs better than missing her head, <<1>> supposes. Goodbye, merciful yet punitive friend.
You did it! The dreugh are pulling back. nnBless you.
Did you find Thorn Lodge?
I hope they find Jofnir alive and well.
It might be time for me to go inside, or at least find some shade.
Things should get back to normal now, and that will be good for business.
This one knew Sees-All-Colors was responsible.
Ooh, this one looks like a killer. nnI like a good killer.
I very much mislike this. Tunnels of earth and rock should not move beneath your feet.
Something doesn't feel right here .
I always had my eye on <<1>>. He cleans up real nice!
Have yourself an Amulet, do you? Abnur's loss is unfortunate, but he knew that failure would mean he was expendable.nnJust as you are.
Good thing the captain spotted pirates on our approach. If she hadn't turned us when she did, we'd be decorating the bottom of the bay.
A Dunmer told me he saw the ghost of one of Ysgramor's Companions. Poor guy must be mad.
A giant stomping across the Rift, then bandits on the roads, now Worm Cultists in the city. I'm sleeping with both eyes open from now on.
The shrine is restored!
Hope what I said about Colors can be kept private. I'd hate to get on her bad side.

Come, let me gauge your strengths. I offer training to Fighters Guild members in some of our special techniques.nnI also have a few things for sale, but only if you're a member of the appropriate standing.
If it isn't the Wormslayer! Only the best for you, my friend. What can I get you?
Heard what you did on the docks. Fine work, my friend. What can I help you with?
Hey, it's the Wormslayer! A round for the Wormslayer, everyone! No more zombies in the lakes hic!
Ah, the hero who defeated the Cult on the docks. A pleasure. How may I help you?
At least we now know what the Reachmen wanted in the mine.
Business is picking up. Let me know if you need something.
I hope they find Jofnir alive and well.
It might be time for me to go inside. Or at least find some shade.
This bow is the only thing I have left of my wife's. She's returned to the Hist, and I will miss her until I die.nnI can't tell you how much it means to hold it once more.
I was thinking I might join the Fighters Guild. See the world, have some adventures.
