Well, while we wait for them to decide who the next mayor is going to be, someone has to tidy this place up and make it presentable.
This one desires the sweet taste of freedom. Perhaps you could dish some to poor Zenkaja?
You'll have to excuse me if I don't shed a tear for my dearly departed husband.
My heart goes out to the many victims of this foul tragedy that has befallen <<1>>.nnSo! Do you need to buy anything?
Find Healer Dalen at Eidolon's Hollow. He needs those hearts!
The traveler returns! Is it done? Are the bones destroyed?
Thank you for saving my family's remains. May Y'ffre bless your travels.
With the focusing crystals in hand, I can complete this control rod and safely reactivate the automaton. While you recover the crystals, I'll make the proper adjustments to the construct.
Quality goods. No questions. Get you something?
The crew of the Albatross knows what you did. If the Queen's Own Navy takes us in, we'll make certain everyone else knows, too.
Seems to be no end to this conflict. Cutting the head off the snake would help our cause tremendously.
We're lucky to have you, adept. I'm no Battlemage. I'm much more comfortable in the stacks than in the field.
Well done, Adept. The essence you've gathered will serve us in good stead.nnNow imbue this energy into the proper tile.
You're the hero of Faldar's Tooth, right?
My lord is very excited to begin the play. As I am. I adore amateur performances.
The marines and I will take charge here. With any luck, we'll have these beasts cleared out soon enough.

We'll load what we can on the Albatross. If we bring a list of what's left to the Dominion, they can do the heavy lifting.nnThe cavern isn't actually spinning, is it? Oh  maybe I'll get to it later. I should sit down.
Make sure you laugh a little. A little bit every day.
From what I've heard things are only getting worse up there. I'd keep my weapon at the ready if I were you.
Sounds like King Fahara'jhad's envoy is ignoring Dame Falhut and refusing to leave the main gate.nnWe're keeping our weapons ready. This may be about to get ugly.
Byz is happy going back to sweep in warm elf houses and cellars, and not caves of scum.
Thank the Green! Where are you coming from? Silvenar or Arenthia? We've been desperate for reinforcements.
The Stonefire cult has manipulated the Colovians into capturing Arenthia. That is where the Mane was taken.
You want to help us? We could use the help.
A friend of Aniel's, huh? Welcome to the Knife.
Until we meet again, mortal. I'm sure the master will have more  "activities" planned for you by then.
Oh! Gall and pox! Dame Dabienne wanted me to tell the duke you were coming here.nnYou saved me back in Koeglin Village! I'm the messenger  the one in the warehouse.
You go kill Elf, then leave! Toothmaul claim caves now! Care not for Elf wars.
Don't let the priest bore you, my friend. And ask Shazah if you have any questions about this Moon Hallowed business. This one's just happy she understood what her sister was talking about.
May the light of Auri-El bring peace to <<1>>.
This is great! Remember to hold a spot for us on the Spearhead!
I'll just rest here a moment until my head stops swimming. Go on, I'll see you later in Shor's Stone.
Most of the attacks occurred along the northwest road. I'd start there if I were you. And travelerwatch your back.
The locals claim my father hunted bears and other animals in these hills. There must be some clue nearby.
I heard about you! You're the stranger who freed Dabienne from the stocks, aren't you?nnSure glad you're here.

Those fools thought they were necromancers. But in their ignorance, they killed and raised everyone inside this facilitynot just those condemned to die. If this place wasn't so well hidden, its effects could've spread to <<1>> itself.
We will see you in Rawl'kha, Hallowed.nnAnd if she is feeling kind, Shazah will fill in Khali on all she has missed.
Damn Drublog. If I had a weapon, I'd slit a few of their throats before they got me.
Impressive. Thanks for the help! Now to pick up the pieces and rebuild it.
That worked out much better than I thought it would.nnI think formal introductions are in order. My name is Tharayya. Pleased to meet you.
There has been so much blood and so much darkness here today. I should attend to these wounded knights.
Did you see how big that thing was? And those teeth!
You made a fool's decision! Did you not see the horror this thing unleashed?
The cultists are inside the ruins but we cannot follow. The doorway is sealed. nnThere seems to be a connection between the welkynd stones here and the spirits that guard the gateway.
How did you get here?
How did you find your way in here?
Others came before you. All who enter will die.
They're gone! What powers you must wield!
They lied to us! The damn Maulborn lied to us! Who's going to cure me now?
I guess I'm lucky I never made it into the quarantine. But you know, I don't feel very lucky. I guess I do have the plague .
Time to head back to Skyrim. I want to see the snow one more time before this plague kills me.
I don't believe it. There must be some mistake. The Maulborn want to help us. They said they were here to do good.
I wish I hadn't been right about the Maulborn. I really wanted there to be a cure for this cursed plague.
I hope that's Yngrel's blood I see on you!
I sense the forest more at peace now.
I'm ready. How do we get out of here?
Oh my  that was quite a rush. Thank you for the experience, new friend!
You are not <<1>>, yet you called me here. How?
I  don't think I'll ever forget those screams. I hope he gets back to his family, some day.nnGo on. Go get that bastard Wormfather. I can get back to the portal on my own.
<The Guardian's Eye hums at a barely-perceptible pitch.>
I am so worried about my fellow priests at the shrine, but Master Aron told me to stay here until things were safer there.
Do I know you?
Meet me at  <<1>>'s longhouse when you're done. If his answers don't satisfy me, we'll put those locks of hair to good use.
By Mauloch's right hand! May the blood spilt be but a trickle next to the tides to come!nnYou have bested me, so I must grant you a boon, if you so wish.
You must be the ones who helped Lienne and Irnand. We got here as soon as we could.
The Worms  ripping my soul apart. Help me!
I can't believe I fell for that. I'm getting soft.
The look on her face was priceless!
Just get me that bottle of wine before I change my mind.nnI think I'm going to need a nice, hot bath when this is all over.
If you'll excuse me, I have healing potions to craft.
I don't want to leave Velyn Harbor, but it's too dangerous to stay!
Velyn Harbor's my home! I don't want to leave!
The militia? Are they all right? I tried to lead them, but the Drublog .
Funny seeing you here.
You tough. Maybe tough enough for Crucible. Maybe not.
It is good to make profit, especially in times of war. The Dominion will pay a good price for these.
Come join us at the Screaming Mermaid when you get a chance. First drink's on me.
Go away. I got no time for you either.
Welcome back to the Isles, adept. We must be wary. This part of Sheogorath's realm is twisted and corrupt.
Whatever it is, I didn't do it!
Sorry. Enough troubles of my own right now. Can't deal with any of yours.
Well, you're a notch above our usual clientele. Make yourself at home.
This is outrageous! I am a captain of the Fists of Thalmor! By what authority does a mere sergeant keep me detained?nnWhen my superiors hear what happened this day, <<1>> will be court-martialed!
Velyn Harbor's been preparing for my wedding, so I have to take the time to meet with the locals.nnDon't worry! I'll still beat you to Dra'bul.
You have your orders, Drublog. Why do you disturb me? Has something gone wrong?
I know you're not a Drublog. You're friends with <<c:1>>, like me. But your trickery did not come fast enough. She's gone.
Please leave me. I wish to mourn my daughter.
What are you waiting for, an invitation? We've got a trap door to explore!
So, you've come to kill me.
Now I need that bath. A nice long soak with a few glasses of this fine wine.nnDon't worry. I'll catch up and meet you at the farm.
Careful in there. Drublog Orcs aren't known for their diplomacy.
By Mauloch's right hand! May the blood spilt be but a trickle next to the tides to come!nnYou have bested me, so I must grant you a boon, if you so wish.
By Mauloch's right hand! May the blood spilt be but a trickle next to the tides to come!nnYou have bested me, so I must grant you a boon, if you so wish.
Allow me to rest for a bit.
Allow me to rest, please.
Eager for a fight, eh? I like you.
Hold on.

I thought we had lost you for a little while there. You seemed to be consumed by the dream much as the king was.nnAfter he returned though, you slept soundly. I knew you were all right then, so I left you to rest. You needed it.
Give me a chance to rest.
I hear you got <<1>> and her crew out of Saintsport. With her on our side, things become a lot easier.
Give me a chance to recover.
That's a nice disguise, but you don't smell bad enough to be a Sea Drake. What are you doing here?
My father was right  I should never have married a Khajiit.nnI wanted to see the world, explore foreign lands, eat exotic foods, not pull my hair out over a moon-sugar addict!
Thank you for agreeing to look for Master Raston. I'm sure he was going to talk to Gulakhan Harrinat. Perhaps he can tell you where Raston's gotten to.
Ah! Please, don't beat me again!
I'm out of shape. Give me a moment.
Are you a minion of the Worm Cult?nnI beg you to stop this. You fools are destroying history with every artifact you desecrate.
target: Are you a minion del Culto del Verme?nnI beg you to stop this. You fools are destroying history with every artifact you desecrate.

source: Choke and die, Sea Drake! I'll spit on your grave.
I don't understand what happened. I feel like my body, my mind, were not my own. A fate worse than death. nnThank you for restoring my mind. Now I must restore my honor.
If you're going to kill me, get it over with.
You completed the quest!
You completed the quest!
Good luck. I'll be in Helane's cabin. Don't forget to stop by after Deregor is out.
I'm not telling you anything, scum! What have you done with Captain Lerisa?
I'm off to join my crew, unless you have any burning questions.
<Captain Helane is unconscious but still breathing.>
This is the part where I trust you.
You get into trouble, you're on your own.
The Staff of Arkay. Take it, use it to strike down these blasphemers.

I would send one of the Spirit Wardens to Wayrest, but after everything we've been through, they need rest.nnI'm glad I can rely on you in these troubled times. The king trusts you, and I know you'll get the message to him quickly.

The staff will reveal circles of corruption among the crypts. There lurk the Bloodthorn Cult's abominations, hidden in pockets of Oblivion.nnPlant the staff in a circle to draw an abomination into our world. Then destroy it!
The Bloodthorn's perversion of my people is ended. The honored dead are at rest once again.
Our war was a long time ago. Once we've cleared out the cult, we'll rebury any bodies they've defiled. Even Breton dead deserve that dignity.nnAlso, I don't want them creeping into town at night.

Alit grease! That's a great idea! Who knew those slimy beasts were good for something? But don't be stingy. You probably need a lot of grease to turn that lever.nnOh, and there are two more levers you need to throw or the door won't open.
Out for a stroll, enjoying the scenery?
These cultists are a real nuisance. I'll report back to Captain Kaleen in a bit. Hope the robes helped.
Hrr! This wretched forest has already taken everything precious to <<1>>.nnGo away!
You made it. Won over the giant with your charm, no doubt.
I'll detain you no longer, my friend. The situation in Gavaudon sounds urgent. We cannot afford for matters there to get any worse.nnI am glad you will be there to ensure they do not. Gods keep you.

Aha! So you returned from Gavaudon with another feather in your cap? Defeating the Ironhand Ogres? Wish I could claim such an accomplishment.nnFrankly, it's an honor to know you. Is there anything you need from me?

The Sacred Lady told me to tell you to talk to an Ordinator.nnBy the way, two people came by and asked for you. A pretty young woman and a dour old man. They said they had to leave the city, but the woman wanted me to pass on her thanks.
A number of Velyn Harbor's citizens joined the militia after you rescued them.nnThey'll protect the town when you're gone. Thank you!
We're being slaughtered here!

Roku spoke of what you did at Velyn Harbor. She says if my champions were dumb enough to challenge you, they deserve their fate.nnI'm not as easy to impress. So tell mewhy do you trespass in my stronghold?
Just get us home.
Is this not the most magnificent inn? The tapestries are so vibrant, the people so friendly!
I've got nothing to say to you.
Hello, stranger. If you're hungry, I've got extra.
Is Malanie dead? Yes? Maybe now I can earn a living wage. Doubtful on this island, but it must be better than before. Right?
You're not another one of those ruffians, are you? Don't you dare lay a hand on me, or you'll get a good wallop!
You're no Steel Shrike! At least, you don't look it. Did you get caught in their raid too?

Ugh. My insides feel like maggot haggis. Guess that batch was a little too strong. Ah well, the next one will be better!nnIt's like my father used to say, "True progress comes from the crashing waves of a maelstrom."
<A large potion sits atop a small book.>
<The monkey screeches happily.>
You made it. Won over the giant with your charm, no doubt.
I only have a moment to talk.
By trusting you with this petition, I acknowledge your actions to save my tribe. I trust you to deliver it intact.
We'll have the Spearhead ready to sail for Betnikh the moment you return with Bhosek's records.
The captain's inside.
Oh. Yes, hello. This is fascinating. Did you know the Dwemer had devices to rapidly mince fruit?
The relic is gone and my people's souls are at rest. I thank you for your choice.
If they do chop off your head, try to keep the blood off the vest. I'll be scrubbing for days elsewise.
You look a proper servant now. Hurry up with those records. I'll be right here, sweeping away.
Hurry on now. You don't want to be whipped. Bhosek's been doing all too much whipping lately.
Tell me more about those firm, deft hands of yours, Jakarn.
This Jakarn is quite charming, for a scoundrel.nnBut I do love scoundrels.

Welcome to Endarwe's Museum of Wonder and Antiquities.nnNormally, I'd tell you to avoid touching anything, lest you defile my sanctum, but the necromancers that came in before you have already ruined everything.

Go to the mine near the Daggerfall cathedral. Plant the spirit's possessions within the soil that belonged to her family.nnThat should awaken her. Then you can learn the truth of this curse and make your decision. Now go!
These two are the ones for me, my friend. You should see what Firn can do with her toes.
Y'ffre's bones! Did you do that to Helthar? That was hilarious!
Go. Leave Helthar alone.
I hear you're to blame for ousting <<1>>. Good riddance. Maybe now the Drublog will settle down and I can finally head back to Jathsogur.nnThank you. Not everyone would do what you did.
Before we leave for Betnikh, talk to the crew. Get familiar with them. It'll be a long trip.

<<1>>'s upset about this. We all are! It's bad for business when the mammoths get loose.nnAlthough, it does say something about the strength of our brewery, doesn't it? Strong enough to put a mammoth to sleep!
The King is pleased with what you've done here, as am I. You will find a generous reward belowdecks.
You need to get to the Silvenar soon, but you should avoid entering the city before talking to him.

I'll rebuild this manor, but not for my father's sake. I think he and my grandmother caused enough trouble here.nnThe new Baelborne manor will be different. It won't be a name to fear anymore. It will be a name to love.
Careful here. These Orcs aren't yet part of the Covenant, but I'm working on that.nnFeel free to check out Stonetooth Fortress. Maybe you'll meet a nice Orc.
I hate them all. The Ayleids, necromancers, the Merethic Society, Endarwe, my father; to Oblivion with all of them!
You are a Khajiit!nnI am <<(c:1>>, the spiritual advisor to ? why, it's you! Wonderful.
Give that fat bastard my best, eh?
Go, my friend. Without the blessings of Jone and Jode, without the completion of the path of the Mane, Khali is doomed. We must go to Dune, walk the Path. I will meet you there.
Perhaps he'll listen to me. For once. I swear, I think it's a miracle of the Divines that any of his students last past the first year.
Go, my friend. I want my sister back, and I want her back now. The path to her freedom starts in Dune. I will meet you there.
Good luck down there, recruit. Make the bastards pay.
I need to prep for our counterassault. Good luck out there.
Go on. Light it.
I still can't believe you destroyed it. Do you know how many brave soldiers are going to die fighting off the Elves?nnI don't even want to look at you.
I see the Countess is out and about town again. nnIt certainly makes me feel better about things.
Don't tell me you agree with this sanctimonious desert rat?
You defeated my cursed body. Never thought I would be free again.nnYou have my thanks.
If you're truly her friend, you'll tell her to ignore this pickled sack of meat!
You have courage. Kasan respects that. Even so, you made a grave mistake.nnThe Covenant will not use that relic for defense only. Remember my words.
So the Countess is in good health again, and all is well in the village.nnHopefully that'll teach people not to get so bent out of shape over a bunch of rumors.

You are formidable to have defeated me in battle. But that was Drodda in control, not I. Find me in Sovngarde if you make your way there. We'll duel again.nnIn the meantime, climb to the summit of this Keep and end that cowardly witch, Drodda.
Give the Captain my regards!
Damn it! You know what this means? All these dead cultists? nnJust more graves I have to dig.
Sometimes, I miss the swamps of my homeland in the Black Marsh. But it is good to be gone from the dry air of Stros M'Kai.
Hey, you gotta let me outta here.
There's no time! Put out these fires. Now!
Thanks to you, I'm pursuing my love of weapon-making. I'm finally happy and Mother's stopped nagging me to fight.
Remember me? You helped me kill that big snake! I decided to ditch my father's old sword for this beauty.
You're not one of Bhosek's Bloody Fists. Lucky for you.
Did you come with my tonic water?
There's always room for more monkeys, that's what my family always says.
Not many of us left, huh?nnCan't say I'm surprised. It's terrible out there. Doesn't make it any better, though.
We lost so many people. The Tardins, the Elwins, the  oh, I don't want to think about this anymore!
Yes?
We're done here. See if I ever offer to partner up with you again.
A precious Khajiiti relic, sold at some merchant's table. The Bright Moons weep tonight.
Greetings Champion, how may I serve you?
What a terrible omlette! It tastes like ashes.
Kalari will be all right, you will see. Just needs some time to deal with what has happened.nnGo, speak to Milk Eyes.
What will I do now? I grew up in Master Hlenir's service.nnMaybe I'll go and become a warrior myself.
Go on, you've earned it!
It can't be! My sweet daughter, dead?
I should be able to write threeno, no, fivescholarly dissertations about this Dremora beard pot. They'll make for fascinating reading!
Once you get used to the smell, these clothes are really quite remarkable.
What a marvelous book! I can't wait to read it.
You won, so stop gloating. I'll get into the Academy next season. But know this, you made an enemy of Renus Falvani when you took my invitation.
What truly makes a Nord, I ask you? Well, his weapon for one. His drinking prowess, certainly. But his shield - that's his true companion!nnBlast it all, where's that thrice-cursed shield of mine!
I know I made the right decision. I don't belong at some fancy academy. I'm heading back to Lower Yorgrim as soon as I can secure passage.
Father lied to me! He said I was powerful! He said I couldn't be defeated! And then you came along. Oh, just leave me alone!
I heard what he said. I don't know if I could have done it either, soldier. Don't worry about us here. There's no need to sacrifice more lives. We'll pull out as soon as we can.
As soon as folks saw you light up that beacon, I felt the tension drain from the village.
I'm already beginning to plan our next field mission. I'm thinking one of the planes of Oblivion. It's been some time since I perused the stacks in Apocrypha, for example.
May the Empyrean Light of Aetherius light your path.
Stars guide your steps.
Bright moons guide your path.
Jakarn said the gate in that cave is never locked because no one ever makes it past the traps.
Now I am going to have to seal up that cave and drain the well before it can be used again.
What's that in your hands there? Seems you've been busy.
The Sergeant can complain and shout all he wants. With that wound, he won't be doing any more fighting today.
If it's not Goblins, it'll be something else tomorrow. I swear this town is cursed.
Go forth and know that Daggerfall and the crown stands behind you.
Every now and then another straggling ogre comes through. I'm just cleaning up now.nnLet's have a drink together when this is all over.
You have been a great help to this community.
Why? Why did you do it? Razum-dar was clear in what he said.
Mercenaries cannot be trusted. And sometimes, neither can <<1>>.
Milk Eyes. Dead on the ground, gnawed by rats? Does Ezzag have to carve you a picture in the sand?
If any of the Bloody Fists ask what you're up to, just tell them you're out for a stroll. Don't mess with the Fists.
Just look at him. He's itching to head for the beach as we speak! Who knows what that little rascal might find?

I'm not accustomed to strangers offering help. My brother and I, we've just had each other for so long.nnThe only thing that matters now is <<1>>'s safety. If you find him, tell him to forget the plant. I won't see him hurt trying to save me.
Don't think because I'm wounded that I won't defend myself. The stranglers won't have much to devour after I'm done with you!
<This Redguard died recently.>
Get going, walker. Zurana's in no mood to speak to you further.
Did you finish helping Bob?

The score was sweet. Priceless paintings from Daggerfall. Irina knew where they were coming ashore, Siraj was her muscle, and I was going to fence it.nnNow my brother's dead and that bitch is too. Sep bites us all, doesn't he?
Hey there! Come here quickly!
You won't just learn the tricks of the trade from me, Sera. You'll learn the trade.

You come to destroy my master?nnI know what you seek. I would tell you a simple riddle, yet you already have the answer in your posession. That rune you hold is the key to releasing me. The living flesh holds the riddle answer no longer.
Have you found my favorite axe? I long to wield it once again.
With you helping Captain Kaleen, we'll get the goods and be on the sea in no time!
Those are the only people I heard Captain Kaleen mention.
You just saved Jakarn a very public execution. Get moving.
You again? What is it this time?
The baron looks hurt. See if he'll tell you what's going on here.
I've recommended we cease investigation, at least until the dead lie down again.nnIt's a miracle any Fists of Thalmor made it out.
You enjoyed every minute of our little adventure. I can tell by the sparkle in your eyes.
Tread lightly. Whatever attacked us is still around.
What can I do for you?
Part of me doesn't want to open the letter, as if the action itself would make the fear of his death a reality.
They're all gone!
Excellent! I can't wait to present this to King Fahara'jad. I'm sure he'll put it to good use!
Go ahead, just speak to it. It can tell you so much about the site.
My friend. It is good to see you again. Please, speak to the woman. Raz will wait for you.
My last arrow. Have to take the rest down the hard way.

Start with Shaman Laganakh. She witnessed Bloodthorn rituals in the Carved Hills. She's waiting by the longhouse south of here.nnCultists were also seen at Moriseli, to the north, and Grimfield, west of here.
I heard of your deeds. Glad you destroyed that thing.nnLambur was right about you. You're welcome on Betnikh any time.
@@Uhh@@ Go away, the stranglers killed your friends. And the one's that turned on me had it coming.
The relic was here, I saw it!
Please, just leave me be.
Odreth's a good captain. He loves the Rangers more than anyone
target: they mean the world to him. He takes it personally if anyone tries to interfere with them or their legacy. That's why he's the captain.

source: Thank you for saving my brother. To know that Sir Hughes is dead and that Vaermina's plot here was thwarted gives me much peace.nnI still mourn the loss of my sweet Lakana though.
So first you freed me, and now you saved the king? You certainly do keep busy. You're an inspiration too. nnI hope we run into each other again.
Follow my advice and those covert Alessians shouldn't give you any trouble.
I'm going to watch this bridge, make sure nothing else moves in. I can see Amadour feeding a troll or something equally disgusting.
I'm afraid something has happened to Zich. He loves Goblin's Delight and eagerly runs up everytime I make a new batch. I hope he comes by soon.
As if some spirit could scare me. I'll just devote the rest of my life to cheating death. That will show her!
Are you ready to free your friend? Not much time left.
These curatives do wonders to help the wounded. You've saved a great many lives today.nnThank you for taking the time to bring this to us.
Thank you again for returning my dear little friend. I hope he doesn't wander off again!
Never thought I'd say it, but I'll be glad to strike a living enemy again.nnI've had enough of undead for one day. Maybe for a lifetime!
Go speak to your Artificer, child. He seems quite agitated.
Daughter, enough. I know you are concerned, but I will hear no more of it.
The Clanmother likes to be obeyed promptly. Remember this, when you are sad you did not listen to Zal-sa.
You have proven your barbaric nature. Be gone.
Murderer! Butcher! You will suffer for your crimes, I promise you!
Please, don't kill me! I have gold. Lots of gold. Kill her. She knows everything!
Pray to Arkay, Orc. Pray hard.
Are you going to murder me, too? Get on with it, then!
Hey, what's a Red Rook doing in our camp! Ha! Just kidding!nnYou do look pretty good in that outfit, though.
Is it done? Is the envoy dead?nnThen let me out of here so I can go rescue my family!
So, ah  unless there is anything else, I should get back to  ah  helping? Helping the good merchant to her valuables. With her valuables! Yes!

Waitaren't you the person who rescued Dame Dabienne from those mad villagers? Yes, I'm certain you are! She described you perfectly. nnDo you have time? You must tell me everything. I can write a song about you!
I've heard your praises from a number of rescued miners. Well done.
Sounds like those ogres are no longer a threat!nnNow we can go on with our lives.
They're finally going to tear down that guillotine! It's about time. I hate living in fear.
Go on. The lamia caves are up ahead.nnI need the matriarch dead.
Even my death failed my people.
The Wyrd Sisters know much more about healing than I do. Thank you for helping them.
Our gambit paid off. The lamias on the shore fled soon after your entrance into the caves.nnWe've broken the back of their army, and are free to press the assault against the Maormer.

So word is you went up to Firebrand and hunted down Sir Hughes. nnGood to know someone around here had the guts to do the right thing. That bastard didn't deserve to live, not after what he did to our Duchess.
He's trapped. Captured with a snare of Daedric magic. He will be made into the ones you have fought, or killed if proven too weak.nnIf you wish to free him, be warned. You may take his place!
This one must find more coin if he is to ever bask in warm sands again!
Something is different. Something has changed.
We must right the wrongs of history and heal the soul of our world. Are you ready to meet your destiny, Vestige?
You are the Hallowed. It is your sacred charge, now, to keep the Claw safe.
Find the Mane, please. Now, of all times, for the Khajiiti people to lose their way  we can't.
My friend! This one is glad to see you. And I am in nowhere near as dire straits as I was last time our eyes met.
I heard you ran the Red Rooks out of town. That should make my work much easier. Thank you.
You killed everyone I love! Why?
I think I might join the Fighters Guild. See the world, have some adventures.
Damn my luck! I chose the wrong time to come home from Greenshade.
Be wary. Drusilla is powerful. You will need all your cunning to overcome her.
This time of year, I'm always worried about the harvest. It's a race to get the food to market before it rots.
I guess we actually did it. The Daggers saved the day. Sort of.
Be careful. Foul magic taints the air. Perhaps your learned friend can shed some light on this dark mystery and help you to bring an end to its source.
By the Eight, why the blazes are you still bothering me?nnGo find that damn Gelvin and get me back my egg.
Ahh, my old friend! Couldn't resist another exploration?nnBe mindful, this one may be a touch more dangerous. Foul necromancy is at work here.
I think this mercenary band might just have a future, after all.

Search the tents around the ruins. <<1>> said she would meet me at the ruins' entry, straight back from the steps.nnTell her not to worry! I will return with Thalmor reinforcements, and drive out these dungy muskarse Sea Vipers!
Bah. With the Dominion in charge at Brindle, you can't walk in town without tripping over an Elf or a cat.
Go on. I'm sure you'll find that hog of a pig rooting around in the northeast alleys.
Maybe she wasn't working with the slavers, but there's still something shady about that woman. Mark my words.
It is over. If not for your wisdom, your mercy  I would surely be dead. I owe you my life, friend.nnCome, let us leave this place.

I can't believe my eyes. The undead are actually receding. For a while there, I thought we were making a last stand here.nnI'm betting it wasn't our brilliant tactics that drove them away though. Conquering Marbruk wasn't their top priority, was it?
This one will remain behind to aid the injured. But you will see Akkhuz-ri again soon.

It seems our circumstances are even worse than I imagined. The corruption of the Shadow Wood expands across the forest. I fear it's too late to contain it.nnWe must find the Shade of Naemon himself, here on this plane, if we are to stop him.
What is that smell? It smells like a kennel full of wet dogs. Or wet Nords.
By the stars, this was a fruitful stop! You're a favorite among the merchants, and I milked it for all it was worth.
You keep walking around, going in and out. I'm guessing this means you're not going to kill me? That's good.
Tazgol's going to be sorry that he missed that show!
You fought well, for an outsider.
A good fight, stranger.
When your family needs help, you drop everything and come running. I don't want to let Haraldar down.
Go on. Check out the crypts. We'll handle things up here.
Really now, if you have any questions you can speak to my father. He's at the main camp to the east.nnOff you go.
Ah, what a grand and glorious day! I just love the great outdoors!
Why would you return Talmo's banner to him? Dominion heraldry has no place in Vlastarus.
Now that Faolchu is gone, perhaps we can start to heal.
A new chapter in Khajiiti spiritual life begins today, Moon Hallowed. And it is all thanks to you. The monks will write of this day for years to come, and your story will become as legend.
I can't wait to see the lizard's face. He won't ever tease me again!
Get low, and keep quiet. The Centurion sent you, right?
Bright Moons! Please, free me.
Yes! You are no cultist. You have come to save Mahazi! Thank you!
Please, I need to be alone.nnI think you can find your own way out.
Blockheaded savages!  You'd think they weren't even part of the Covenant the way they're treating me.
Ha! These Colovians were like wheat before the scythe.
So, your truthiness overcomes all! My felicitude winds around you like a warm fog.nnGive me those meats and I'll expose <<1>>'s perfitudidness.
<The air around the table vibrates gently as the spell holds. The house is protected, for now.>
I feel strong again, fully healed.nnWhere's my father? I must go to him.
I think I'll practice on locals before heading to Stormhold.nnFirst impressions are everything, as my father used to say.
You impress me, traveller. Few can defeat me in a game of riddles.
I sure appreciate you stepping in to help that mage.
We're going to drive those Red Rooks out of Crosswych, just you wait and see.
This won't end well. And it's all on you, my friend.
Hello there. I hope you don't mind me playing. The music helps soothe the anxiety.
You're going to hand the relic to those fools? I cannot remain with someone who would make such a choice!
Well? Do you want the gold or not?
You're a bigger fool than I thought. You're no shipmate of mine!
Hello
You destroyed something that might have brought us peace. You've doomed my brothers. If I never see you again, it'll be too soon!
I cannot sail with someone who willingly dooms enemies to such a fate.
Thanks to you, Camlorn is no longer under Faolchu's mangy paw.
Hello
I'm glad you're all right. <<1>> will speak with you now.nnHe forbade me to speak further.
You return! Please, tell me. How did <<1>> die?
Hi
Go  kill the betrayers. Save  Dune.
I'll warn the captain and the others. Hurry to the fortress!
Be careful with the package.
Any luck? I just used my last bandage.
You've returned. You have questions.
I'm too late. Too late.
That bastard followed me in here. Didn't think those big ones could fit into this house. Nasty creatures, really.
I am glad you came through in one piece, Hallowed. Um  perhaps you can help vouch for me to the Queen? She continues to make jokes about treachery. I do not like it.
Your assistance with the Maormer is most appreciated my friend.
What do you want?
So Sir Edmund's in the hot seat now. Hope he handles it better than Sir Hughes didnnAfter everything that's happened, I'm not sure I'm staying in the order anyhow.
Step lightly! Fenlords do not keep lazy servants. They could be on us in a flick of a tail!
Thanks to you, I can rest now.
Jakarn told me what you did. I'm impressed. The Orcs were too, so I've been told.
Well, I guess our little tryst is off for the time being. I'll head back to the ship, as soon as Irien's not looking.nnThat woman has nails like a duneripper.
For what it's worth, I think you did the right thing, destroying that relic. Magic that powerful should not be in the hands of Men.
You did a hard thing, the right thing.
It's all right Matilda. We'll be away soon.
Talk to them if you wish. This is simply how things are, in our clan and others. I understand that, even if I don't accept it.
This one is as he was in life. Merely a mote in the lunar light, floating where the Bright Moons take him. As are we all, in the end.
Felari shall keep you in her prayers to the Bright Moons, my friend.
You should have listened to Captain Kaleen. She was right about the artifact.
I commend you again on choosing to keep the relic for the Covenant. But <<1>> tells me we must hasten to Glenumbra.
You've made it  down here  just to die. Aldmeri dog.
So, we're keeping the artifact. While the captain supports your decision, I'm not sure I agree.nnI'm glad I wasn't in your shoes, my friend.
I hear the captain isn't too happy with you about that relic. But at least these Orcs are joining the Covenant.
I have much to discuss with the Bishop and Gharesh-ri, my friend. I'm sure we will see each other again. You are the Hallowed, after all.
The proud city of Daggerfall greets you. Can I help you with something?
Nice work. I'll keep an eye out for more. I'm sure they're coming from Cloud Ruler Temple.nnLet Hjorik know you cleaned out this batch.
Urn  dangerous. Cultists summoned terrible  killed them. Take urn to <<1>>. Find <<2>>. Safe with her.
If you knew where a bunch of dangerous criminals was stashing all their stolen goods, would you have guts to go check it out?
How did you get through the barrier? Speak quickly, stranger. We're all on edge.
Speak to Vanus Galerion in Skywatch. He's expecting you.
No mystery where to find Lokra. Check the docks. She'll be there, staring at your ship  if she hasn't already snuck aboard.
Welcome to Vulkhel Guard! I must attend my Queen at the moment, but I hope you enjoy your time in my fair city.
I should have done more to fight the vampires. I'll make it up to Sud-Hareem someday.
This wasn't supposed to happen. We were supposed to save At'avar at the last moment.
Well, that was fun, wasn't it? All right, maybe fun isn't the right word. But you were glorious!nnAngof is finally dead. We can't thank you enough for what you've done.
Can't you see that I'm trying to read?
I know I saw that book around here somewhere.
Was it twenty coins from the Salted Wings? Or twenty five? nnSorry, sorry. A tax collector's work is never done, you know!
Just having a little sip! Don't  don't tell anyone. It's a secret, just you and me.
Oh, excuse me. Just praying for my son. He's on the front lines in Cyrodiil. nnI know what he's doing is important, but I can't help but wish he was here at home with me.
Oh, hello! Are you looking forward to the Queen's speech too? Going to be a great moment, a great moment.
Have you seen Doralin? She was supposed to help me set the table. Probably off sneaking a drink again, if I know her.
Marvelous view from up here, don't you think?
A little privacy, please? These are some sensitive materials.
Don't mind Kuzda. She'll be finished soon.
You've done it! You've walked paths in darkness and come out the other side  into the light.

I will admit, Hallowed. The words of the Moon Bishop affected me deeply. But your victory here  the scent of your return to our living world. The dawn of a new day for our allies. It fills my heart with hope.
Your actions today humbled me, Hallowed. That you would work to secure the future of my people so earnestly  truly, the Bright Moons do shine down upon you.
The Moon-Hallowed cannot travel the Two Moons Path with such corruption going on. We need to clean this city for all to be right with our people.
Sorry, hunter. I only had enough for one bounty. I'm saving the rest of my coin for more of this fine brew.
Senche are terribly dangerous beasts. This one tires of the hunt.
By the Green! One of those damned Senche got me.
I'm going to be the one to claim the prize! Even if I have to kill every Senche out here to do it!
Ungh, finally. Soldier, I'm not going to stay conscious much longer. You have to tell the Centurion.
Good to see Dominion troops in Cropsford. I feel safer with armed Altmer around.
You made it out of Ilmyris alive? How  unexpected.
My friend the traveler! Zadala's meeting went well  she hopes she's glad to see you again?
This is my fishing spot. Go find another!
What does my lord command?  Wait, who is my lord again?  It's all so muddled.
One by one, Naemon and Pelidil exposed my servants to the crystals, until their mortal minds cracked and groaned under the strain.

Dark Moons! These crazy Bosmer make no sense! Hazazi comes to negotiate on behalf of Queen Ayrenn, to hear their grievances, and all they do is dance and jest!nnHazazi has only been here a short while and already he hates this village.
<<1>> needs your help. You must go now, before it is truly too late.

This one would ask a favor. If this Thalmor mage turns Razum-dar into a monkey, you must exact vengeance.nnOh, and you would need to track down Pelidil on your own. Raz hopes this will not be the case, though.
Those cultists are some nasty pieces of work. Go carefully along that part of the riverbank.

So you're the one who's going to accompany the cat on this guar-brained scheme of his? nnI hope you realize what you're up against. These traitors in our city have sought to stir up rebellion since the day King Camoran joined the Dominion.
Thank you for delivering my message to Hissmir.

Another tourist? Rare to have so many visitors in this part of the Valenwood. Didn't you hear? It's much safer behind the shiny new walls of Marbruk. nnEven King Camoran hesitates to venture into the Court of the Wilderking.
Kaushur is hoping to leave this wretched place soon. The only ones crueler than the combatants are the odds-makers.
You came from Jorunn's Stand. Did the general send you?
Have you seen the mewling hounds they call warriors here? They are nothing before the might of Lugrun!
Hey there! Bit busy here, if you don't mind. Been a long day.
My cousin died in the arena! He died like a true son of Sovngarde!
You've no idea how thankful I am that you're not a Daedra. The gods are merciful.
I'm already prepared to retake this town once again.
Dawnbreak will be ours. We beat these Daedra once, we can do it again.
Why oh why are you pestering me? Let me enjoy my fire in peace.nnShoo now. Shoo.
Please, for the sake of our people, defeat the <<1>>.
Fildgor has departed this place and the spirits return to their eternal sleep. Tell me what happened here.
The moons sometimes force us to walk strange paths. They are not always the most fragrant, swiftest. But, ultimately, they lead us where we should go.
My scales still leak blood, but with time I'll heal. I must document everything that has happened here. nnThe people of Murkwater will never forget what you have done for us.
Come, follow!
I will watch this path for any suspicious strangers.
Every day that this place is shut down is a day I'm losing gold.nnSo what happened out there? Do you bring me good news or bad?
What can I do for you?
Part of me doesn't want to read this diary. I think that would make what happened to my cousin all the more real.
I lost my family! They're all gone!
My sister is going to be so happy that you saved me.
<The guard no longer responds having fallen back into a deep sleep.>
Get out of here. You've worn out your welcome.

The Ra-Netu have returned to the sea. The docks will soon smell of dead fish again instead of dead people.nnAnd you! Right off the boat and you slay the necromancer? Surely Tu'whacca sent you to deliver us from this  difficult situation.
Hurry through the Roost upstairs to reach Blackheart's Cove. You'll find the Captain there.

You dealt with the spriggan matron, didn't you? Wish I could have helped.nnWe'll wait around until the trolls leave. Without the influence of the matron, they won't stick around here for long. Then we can get back to business.
I made my way back here. On my own. No thanks to Boss Thulvald. nnI really need a warm bed in a nice safe inn. And a good meal. And probably a new job.
Good work humiliating my brother! He needed to be taken down a peg.
We meet again, Hallowed. Be cautious. The path ahead is fraught with danger, and the sky darkens above us.
<Egolor lies on the floor in a pool of his own blood.>
I told you, I'll get the money to Many-Eyes as soon as I can.
Please, no more. I'll get Many-Eyes her money as soon as I can!
Quick, untie me before she returns!
I'll get you back someday.
Good fighting there. Garnikh won't forget you.
Nothing more for you here. Keep moving.
So was the hunt successful? Did you find out what nefariousness our good Commander Yjarnn is up to?

You might want to get back on your boat, seafarer. The dead are crawling from the sea and they have overtaken the docks.nnThere is nothing to be done. We just have to pray to Tu'whacca that they wander away.
It took a brave soul to charge in there. I hope your courage was rewarded.
I have spoken for the good of the clan. You are free to tell Lokra whatever you wish.
Perhaps an outsider's opinion will convince Lokra, as she doesn't seem to listen to those of her clan.
Have you met our enemies?
You have done well.
The waters will clear soon, now that you've fixed whatever troubled Alten Corimont.nnIt's a sign.

So you found out what that Dominion spy was up to, huh? Glad someone else could. I can't do everything myself.nnCleaning up this xanmeer's work enough. Then again, all these ruins need a good cleaning, inside and out, if you catch my meaning.
I'll never admit this to Captain Lerisa, but I think you did the right thing. A Breton king as ambitious as Emeric should not be handed that kind of power.
I can't believe he stood me up. The nerve. I mean just that I was looking forward. To working with him.nnBah! That's it. I'm done!
I've heard  you're the one who figured out the Dominion's part in our recent troubles. True? Must be nice.nnWell, some of us have troubles of our own, and you don't hear us begging for help.
Fobbing cheats! I just let a full cargo hold of timber go for half its value! I don't like the way these Redguards negotiate.nnI'll never get square with S'rashi at this rate.
Well. What are you doing on my boat?
No  don't make me look at him! The Dark Husband is here!
Thanks for freeing us. It's about time we got out of this horrid swamp.
My mind reels with what we've accomplished here. I can't wait to get back to Hatching Pools and spread the tales of your exploits.nnThank you!
<This ward prevents any entry into the temple.>
The Bright Moons are with you, Hallowed. Khali will be a credit to her name, leading her people with bravery and strength. And Shazah's wisdom will be more than a match for the Dark Mane's treachery.
You  you're not crazy! You can't be corrupted by the whispers either?
I don't believe a word Jakarn says, but there's just something about him. He's fascinating.
Jakarn's gorgeous. He could rob me any time.
I don't really believe he's a captain. He looks so good I don't care.
You killed them! Those people were my friends. I should've been the one to put down the crazy bastards!
Blood and faith! Are you real? Can you hear me? Please, get me down!
Begone, servant. Do your work and stop bothering me.
You do not carry yourself like a servant. Best see to that, if you wish to avoid a beating.
We did it. We held. But at what cost?
What do you want?
Touch the stone pillar on the rise behind us. nnShow me the enemies that you would have me share with your Dominion.
I'm glad Ezzy's going to stick around. I'd have missed that old cat!
Now that <<1>> is out of the way, I'll run this Caravan properly and fairly. You have my word.

For our little operation to work, everybody's gotta watch everybody else. The dealers watch the players, the game bosses watch the dealers, and <<1>> watches the managers. Me? I watch everybody. But today, I'm watching you.
Thank you so much for helping this one, stranger. Tand promises to be a better life mate to Sind.
Bright moons and long life to you, walker-friend. We will remember you, always!
Will my brother learn from this, I wonder? Father is right. He doesn't deserve a husband like Sind.
I cannot wait to see the look on Muzag's face when I return his son to him. It's good to earn points with your boyfriend's father, yes?
Did you find anything?
You did it. You saved my father.nnI'm sorry I ever doubted you. You have more than earned our trust.
Good luck on many travels, my friend. Am sure we will meet once again.nnI will spend some time with these monks. Their culture is very fascinating. One wonders what one must do to become one?
This business is none of your concern, creature. Leave the Hand where it lies or your end will come even sooner than already foredained.
You're the mortal who's interfered with my creatures in the bog, aren't you? Don't bother to tell me your name. You won't need it if you continue to trouble me.

I always knew it was the guts of the guardian that gave it powers, but I never dreamed it would be so easy to augment those powers. nnDew bugs, thunderbug bellies, and hive seeds. They're everywhere around here!
Unless you have questions of me, I will soon be on my way. We should both search the forest for other signs of Naemon's corruption. nnI fear at some point, we will have to confront Naemon himself.
You've made it through alive. The other Keepers must be dead, then.nnA part of me wishes it were not so.
The moons shine upon you, friend, and your lizard is spared the stewpot! Congratulations!
<The corpse of <<1>> has already begun to decay. It will be unrecognizable in a few days.>

The Stormfists have three supply wagons with them. Set them on fire and we'll send the entire camp into panic!nnThen light the signal fire and find Fildgor. If he finishes whatever foul ritual he's performing, it will mean the end of the kingdom!
Hurry, champion. I can feel my essence slipping away.
Find that Khajiit! I can't believe she'd turn on her own like this!
I have waited for centuries. And waited  and waited. Do you know how boring that can be?nnBut now you are here. Just as Meridia foretold.
I thought we would get to go home after the keystone was found.
I haven't swung my axe once since we got here, and you did all the work. Well at least I'll get paid. Haha.

What I wouldn't do to be in a nice, safe place. A tavern somewhere, maybe. Warm. A pint of ale. Some good company.nnInstead, I'm in Coldharbour. If Molag Bal's minions don't kill me, Skordo surely will.
Wha what happened? How did I get down here?
I'm very busy. Can't you tell?
Look for Neramo to the north. Just follow the road and look for his tent.

Very few would dare to enter the Prince of Murder's realm of their own choosing. Your action consists of equal parts bravery and stupidity. I think, in this case, that's exactly what we need.nnWe've been waiting for you, planewalker.
You are spikeball champion! This one reminds you that spikeball can be lucrative as a profession, and he would be honored to manage your career.
Who are you? How did you get here? Leave me alone!
Blackheart is dead, but he won't stay that way forever. Let's destroy his skull and prevent him from ever returning.
I'm sorry I lied to you. I  I hope we can still be friends.
Keep running, I'm right behind you!
Well, go on then. No worries, I'll be fine. They haven't made a cage that can hold this knight. Not yet, at any rate.
Oof. Thanks. I don't know how much more of that my ribs could handle.
Praise to Auri-El! The six Elder Scrolls are all in our possession. We must ensure that they remain with us, where they belong!

This is preposterous! Asteril has risked her life for the Dominion more times than I can count. She is one of my best officers.nnI refuse to believe this irresponsible slander until I have spoken with her myself.
If <<1>> survived the Dominion's initial attack, I'm certain he can help.
Spies! There are spies everywhere! And assassins!
Ezbreba is grateful for your kindness.
Name and  blood and bones, Lyris Titanborn!
Isn't he cute? We are going to be closer than ever now.
You've been good for the Shadowscales, outsider. If I'm ever asked to give you our gift, I'd make it quick and painless.
You restored us, outsider. It's like you  unhatched the egg.
I'm glad you councilled Bowenas well. Everyone deserves a second chance.
By Malacath's bloody mace, you did it!

Now you are negotiating with a forest spirit who calls himself a king? With all those floating leaves, Hazazi thinks he looks very silly.nnDo you really think this is going somewhere? Or is it just a waste of time?
The Hist tree will most likely die soon, but I accept your decision. May the scholars' efforts aid you well against Molag Bal.
I appreciate it when a beautiful monster needs something. That usually means you can trust her.nnAt least for a while, anyway.
Now that was a battle worthy of your greatness! Congratulations!
Welcome to Longhaven. Used to be a busier place, before all this trouble with the mist. But we won't let that be an excuse for poor hospitality.
So you made it through the mist. Your will is stronger than I expected.

Reason with this mad Dunmer! You'll have to kill some of the clan, but there are those of us who only want to coexist alongside the living without harm. Wouldn't it be better to have us as allies to call upon?
The amulets are given?
<The statue holds the Gem of Courage.>
I don't know what that well-dressed man just did, but I'm going to bet it's very bad for us.
<This strange contraption is surprisingly heavy and would take several people to move.>
Don't worry. Girin and I will get in there soon enough.nnIn the meantime, keep Indaenir out of trouble.
The kagouti thought themselves clever to coat their tusks with poison, but the Tree knows all. Its roots will soon feed on the kagouti who burned its blood.
<The statue holds the Gem of Courage.>
<The statue holds the Gem of Courage.>
Suit yourself. I'm getting out of here. There's something odd out there. Something strange to the look of the mist .nnAnyway, I'm heading to Woodhearth for a belly full of drink and a soft fur mat.
Defeat the king and be done with it.
Kill me if you must, Orc. I swear, I will rise from the very grave to make an end of you.
Get this door open, Targoth, and let's end this!
What have I done?
How did you do with those Black Daggers?
Go, Targoth. Aid our warchief.
You've returned. What do you have to report?
Thank you for your able council. May bright moons light your path as they light Ezreba's path to forgiveness.
See you in <<1>>. Going to lie down in a bit.
Quickly! Secure the gates!nnThe Maormer must not take the city!
Are you  are you from <<1>>? They said they would send help.
If the gods reward hard work, we've got something coming to us!
With a little luck, we'll have this cleared away before the tide comes in.
Never far from trouble, are you?nnWord reached the palace that Aldmeri forces were here, so the king sent me right away. Looked like many of the Elves were already dead. Where did they come from?
How may Manuk be of service? This one has many fine wares.
The prisoner has paid the blood price for his crimes.
You've done a great service to Greenhill. I'd love to talk, but I really have to finish this inventory.
Merani is really improving her archery skills, don't you think?
Sharp claws, this one is very glad Ezreba will stay with us. She is a bright moon in our sky.
Heard what you decided. Glad Ezreba's going to stick around. Like that cat.
You torment me even in death!
Kada wishes you a bright day and pleasant journeys.
You have done us a great service. May the forest always provide for you.
Thalar cannot offer you enough thanks.
Where is Trela? She was supposed to pick up her meats.
The prisoner has paid the blood price for her crimes.
You monster! My murder wasn't enough?
The prisoner has paid the blood price for her crimes.
Necromancy? Beast! Defiler! Arkay hound you to your grave.
The prisoner has paid the blood price for her crimes.
I hate you. I hate you so much. Why would you do this to me?
Did you make it to Haynote?
Well, you got the job done, though you were gentler than I would've been.
I'll never trust the Midnight Union again, I can tell you that.
I can't hold him for long. Go, before he overtakes me. Tell my master we were successful.
Quickly, return to the courtyard. <<1>> must know of our success.
I heard about Bruma. Sounds like Hafza is out of business. Maybe we should give up on this place altogether.
This day has just gone from bad to worse.
Good job in the Haven my friend. That'll make these seas safe for once.
Thanks to you, we'll be able to float the Prowler off this beach at the next high tide.
Ah, to see out of Khajiit eyes again! Zur hates being caged in that dark place.
What are you doing? Kill that thing before it eats me alive!
Hey there. Buy something, for old time's sake?
Hey, good looking. Long time.
Well, now. What brings you to our humble abode?

Well look who's here. The hero of Betnikh! nnIf you've come to recruit me, I must decline. I'm done sailing, and there's a rich Breton noble over there who could really use a friend.nnTake care of yourself.
Fancy meeting you here. Glad to see you doing well. This is a class above the Screaming Mermaid, I'll give it that.
Now you're a welcome sight!nnI'd chat, but Captain Marck has me testing all the rigging before we set sail again. I'd imagine the debacle at Koeglin Lighthouse made him a bit more cautious.
Well look who it is. Well met, my friend!
Oh, it's you. Yeah, I'm not interesting in talking. Go bug Mekag.
I had not expected to see you again! I'm glad you're still alive.nnIt was a hard choice, staying with Kaleen or Lambur. Ultimately, I'm doing more serving Fahara'jad than I would as a sword for hire.
If it isn't my fine partner from our expedition in Betnikh.

I think I'm just about done with Neramo. All we've done since I joined him is talk about expeditions, not actually join any.nnStill, a berth is a berth. I'll stay with Captain Marck until I find something better.
You! Get out of here. I don't want to see you ever again!
Well met, my friend. You look well.
Well now, a familiar face. How good to see you. Honestly, I'm beginning to wonder if I'm on the wrong ship.
We're here! Daggerfall! At last!nnNow I just need to convince Telonil that a cafe is the right investment.
My friend, good to see you! See this hand? It works again. Found a very talented healer in Aldcroft who put the bones right back together.nnI've put my sword through a few Elves since. Felt good.
Well now, look who it is. The hero of Betnikh.nnI'd wondered if we'd see you again some day. Guess I was right. Lambur owes me dinner.
Oh, it's my dear, brave friend from Stros M'Kai. What a pleasure to see you again.
You are brave to face Kaleen once more. I am glad you have come. She needs more around her who are not blinded by patriotism.
Ah. I erect the spine of respect.
Turn back. You aren't welcome here.
I heard what you said about Grida. Is it true?
Thank you again. I am very much looking forward to returning to my wife.nnI hope she will be as happy to see me.
Thank you, again   I hope you understand my confusion. I have waited and mourned so long.nnI feel I should be angry at him, but I am just  I am just so happy right now.
Never seen you here before. Just got drafted? What'll you have?
Thank you again. I had forgotten what it feels like to feel free.
No idea what to do with this horse. Fertilizer, perhaps?

Sylvain's fertilizer always doubles my yield. And it smells like roses to boot. Just between you and me, I sometimes roll around in it before spreading it in the field. Sure beats taking my monthly bath.
One day I'll escape from this blasted temple. I'll scour all of Tamriel until I find you. Then, I'll turn you into a hat.
I have given you your reward, you have no more business with me.
Greetings and welcome to the Mages Guild Hall! What is it that you have there?
If you found me, someone else will. I will be ready.
That doll was my only toy as a child. We had hundreds of adventures together. Being reunited with her has brought me more joy than you can imagine.
I fear that justice would have been better served by my death. nnI pray your judgment does not prove to be a mistake for the future of the Covenant.
If you're lost, Cropsford is northeast of here. If you hit Drakelowe Keep, you've gone too far.
If you see Niro again, tell himvery politely, pleasethat I'll handle it. He doesn't need to worry, and he certainly doesn't need to come here and see me.
I hoped Hisham would be with you, if I saw you again. Fool is still clinging to his dream of farm life.

When I went to sea with Captain Kaleen, I didn't expect it to be quite so lonely. I miss my home. I wonder if I made the right choice.nnStill, I'm staying with Lambur. I took this path, and I won't step aside now.

You know, it's strange how memories keep coming back to me. When we first arrived in Wayrest, I didn't remember it at all. Now I'm remembering all sorts of things.nnI think I've found a place here with Captain Marck. I owe that to you.
We've a lot to do, rebuilding the camp. But it beats having our innards ripped out by Daedra.
It's a relief to study without the constant demands from the Covenant military. I could not care less about Cyrodiil and Emeric's damned war.
The Crowns have been pushing King Fahara'jad. They seek to ban any Guild member that studies in Eyevea from working with the military. It's just as well, if you ask me.

Ah, wayfarer. Eyevea is like a dream come true! Especially the tradescraft! It's so easy to gather spell components! Do you have any idea how expensive it is to import frost herbs through to Alik'r desert?
A centralized, readily accessible, and above all neutral port for every nation in Tamriel. Research aside, the trading opportunities here are amazing!

You know, if the Guild plays its cards right . Just think of all the coin we could make in trade. We could find ourselves in a very good position. If the Cyrodiil situation ever stabilizes, of course.

High King Emeric knows well how to play the diplomat. While officially he's been neutral on the topic of Eyevea, he's privately been highly supportive. He knows Guildmaster Vanus values his friendship.
Guildmaster Vanus asked me personally to come! Said he wanted to be sure our kin were represented in the heart of the guild. Can you imagine?
Hah! This place is amazing! Some High Elf just got done telling me, where she comes from, they respect their Mages. Coming to Eyevea feels like coming home.
Me maw cried when I left to come here. Said I'd been stolen by Elves and wizards, and that I'd end up a slave in Oblivion. Hah! As if I could ever be a Daedra's slave!
Ah, a civilized magical society. I've put so many faces to names I've only seen in letters. It will be nice to speak frankly about our craft. And not be the "town seer". Hah!
I've heard the whispers, seen the looks. Some think us Nords are a poor fit for magic. I say, clearly someone has to keep the rest of these fools in line. Hah!

Ahh, adept! This morning I got into an argument with one of those shortie Elves. He was arguing that magic is the most efficient solution to any problem. So I punched him in the face!nnWe're going for drinks later. I like this place.
I would have thought Eyevea's return would call out more of our brethren from House Telvanni. But no. Perhaps someday this neutral ground will help draw them back into the fold.
The Tribunal takes a longer view on the conflicts in Cyrodiil. The Three approve of our presence on Eyevea. Sotha Sil himself hopes for a chance to visit, I hear!

The centuries of hatred between my people and  most of Tamriel seems somehow petty in a place like this. There's so much to be gained through collaboration. Perhaps one day, Dark Elves will walk proudly in the lands outside Morrowind.
A secluded island, just for Mages, where we can all do our work in peace. Free from the outside world's politics and horrors. Really? No one else sees this gilded tree for its rotten roots?
My colleagues think this place is far too good to be true. I'm hopeful. I choose to let the river take us where it wants.
This experiment is doomed to failure, mark my words. You've seen the Dark Elves here, right? "All Mages are equals" is a bitter root in my mouth.
This one is so happy to be here! Such an excellent idea. And such delightful fragrances! Sharp claws and Bright Moons to you, adept-who-has-made-this-happen.
Eyevea was a myth, told to tiny Mage cubs. Now you have reached into the past, and legend, and pulled it into the real world. More nonsense like this sounds like an excellent idea!

This one hears others worry about how long Eyevea will last. What does it matter? Gain everything you can now, and worry about whether it will last later. Spend time worrying and you waste the time you have.
Eyevea is ideally placed. A remote but accessible location for the elite to congregate. Well away from the chaos of mainland Tamriel. If you ask me, this is a long overdue asset for the Guild.
Fivefold venerations, adept. All of our people feel great pride in Valaste, for the role she played in your adventure. In her name, High Elves across Tamriel plan to donate tomes to Eyevea's library.
Stars above, Eyevea is a High Elven dream. We gain all the benefits of collaboration with the other races without having to  you know. Actually leave the Summerset Isles. Ideal!
I love this place! I can actually get into real, lively debates about arcano-magical phenomenon. Nobody "defers to my wisdom" or tries to change the subject.nnA Nord even hit me. Amazing!
Being here is quite invigorating, adept. I've been a Greenspeaker for so long . I'd forgotten you could cast spells to harness fire, or change the weather, or even summon an angry Daedra. Amazing!

After living deep in the Valenwood all my life, it's such a difference to be here on Eyevea. I can see the sky, smell the sea air  I didn't expect allergies, though. Something about these mushrooms . Choo!
I can't believe you let her stay. The Green damn you, traveler! A cancer at the heart of our wood.
Comrade. It is good to speak with you again.
Just leave me to die. I wouldn't accept your help and you'd be better off not offering.

Thank you for the sand. Sometimes, after a long day, I miss my life with Rasha. Travelling where our whims took us, living by our swords, seeing exciting places every day. But the Way of the Sword is no longer my path.
This one has heard reports. You've kept busy. Good! You fit in now more than ever. nnHow did things go?
So, have you decided to help us against the evil Wood Elves?

As far as I can tell, the lamias and the Wood Elves don't get along very well. Even though the snake thing saved me, I'm not sure we can trust either of them.nnStill, they may be your best chance for finding a way into this tower.
Kazirra will be very interested in hearing about all this.
The people of Arenthia owe you a great debt, traveler. You will always be welcome within the walls of our city. But your tale does not end here, I think.
You! Yes, you! <<1>> needs you, immediately!
This is an outrage! I demand <<1>> be taken into custody!
We'll take the marines with us when we sail to <<1>>. I hope to see you there.
Any luck securing a copy of the treaty?
The Dominion must understand our position. The free people of <<1>> cannot make enemies with one hand and friends with the other.
She's going to stay. I can't believe you and Bowenas believe she can change! Once you've touched that kind of darkness. The Green take you both!
It doesn't matter. The tempest is coming. Nothing can stop it, not even  her.
<<1>>'s inside resting. You have five minutes.
Ambassador <<1>> isn't here. And if he was, he'd be far too busy to entertain the likes of you.
Is it over? We can stay? I almost find it had to believe.nnThank you though. You have no idea how much.
If you've come to tell me I'm going to lose my leg, just turn around and leave.
Balag noticed that you are still here. I can help you with something more?
What have we here? Another would-be champion? nnLet me guess. You've come to honor us with a display of prowess mere mortals could only dream of possessing.
There's so much more to learn about Ayleid wells. Unlocking their mysteries will lead to greater understanding of the Ayleids themselves, I'm sure.
The privy is back beyond the gate. Or did you need something else?
Hello my lovely. This is quite the year for talent, as well as beauty.
Thank Akatosh you found my new robes. If I heard another joke about my "holey robes," I think I would have stabbed someone.
Take a tip, friend. Don't stay long in Bruma.
I have digging to do and you're in my way.
Who is this, now? A paying customer, here to cheer on the combatants? Or are you something more?

There's no way I can properly thank you for what you've done. This is the first good luck my clan's had in months. This means we can stay here and start over.nnWherever you go, and whatever you do, you'll always be a champion of the Driladan.
I can't afford to wait here much longer. I came to help assist those fleeing the darkness in the forest, but very few have come this way.nnI hope this does not mean they have all simply perished.
My silver flute has a much sweeter tone than the one I've been using. I'll be able to lift some spirits with this in hand!
I'm lucky you wandered by when you did. But then again, I'm always lucky.
Thought I was ruined, but that <<1>> says <<2>> will pay for the kwama to live in that cave.nnI'm not above taking coin from crazy folk. Might even be enough to repair my ship!
Well, you're back but I know what you're going to say, so don't bother. Cousin Asvorn won't give me any more money. That smug, cheap bastard.
Thank you for news of Tertius. I won't sleep easy until he's back with word of Donus.
You honor me with your presence, walker.
If you touched anything, you'll answer to me.

A great wind blew, and many ships were dashed against Khenarthi's island. But you strengthened the Great Tree, despite her anger! <<1>> thrives once more.nnMay your actions show Khenarthi our goal is righteous. May she bless us with favorable winds.
My no-good cousin's not getting any more gold out of me!
You again? Please, I have nothing more to say about it.
MmmMMmmf MMMF!
Please let me know if you find anything. Even if it's just something that confirms she's gone, knowing would be better than this.

Why are you wasting time? My father did not instruct you to relax here and then go after the Withered Hand .nnYou are Ash'abah now. You have a job to do. Go to Tu'whacca's Throne. We will see each other again soon enough.
The Wood Elves have fallen. My eggs shall be returned to my nest and my people shall be safe.nnThe Shadow Walkers shall be lost without their leaders. The day is ours!
So you've returned! I thank you again for your help in the Hollow. Dracien and Bakkhara are lost, but I am pleased we remain to tell their stories.
I hope Hannura appreciated the fish. I like to send her some as often as I can.
Plenty of salvage in a town like this
target: think I'll stick around for a while longer. That dead messenger will slow Marcellus down.

source: The fish you brought will make a nice meal. Perhaps I should invite some friends over to share.
I know this may not be the way you would normally deal with a problem, but it's the only way to make my clan trust you.nnNow, let's go and cause as much chaos as we can!
Begone, bandit. I'll never join <<1>>!
This one  feels odd.
I hope Jafola makes it out of Bruma alive. That town's a sinking ship.
Saldir becomes less reliable all the time. I need to find a new supplier. The wounded here can't wait for Saldir to saunter into town.
I quiver like a leaf in the wind to think of what we'll learn from these ruins.nnWe'll be careful, of course. It would be unfortunate to allow something like this to happen again.
I don't know how I feel about these strange bugs. But if <<1>> doesn't mind, who am I to disagree?
What did you see in that temple? I heard it's full of watery spirits!
So much destruction! Thank goodness you were here to help rebuild the ship!
Greetings, O my friend. You are most welcome in our home. Without your intervention, the city might well have been lost.
The docks have been reclaimed?  We are so grateful. nnMy father is a kind-hearted man, and without imports the city would starve. I wish the Crowns could see that.
Tu'whacca bless you. Some may name you heretic for striking our risen dead, but in this house you are a hero. Be welcome.
It is our duty as Ash'abah to assist the king if he calls upon us. I only wish he had called on us earlier. nnPerhaps this terrible poisoning could have been avoided.
I heard rumors of rats and all manner of lunacy in the Mad God's chateau. How dreadful! We're glad to have you back in Tamriel, safe and sound. Do you need to restock on any provisions?
Cordial greetings and welcome to our toweran isle of knowledge amidst a vast sea of ignorance.  nnHave you come for training?
Well met. I'm the resident librarian. We don't have much, but what we have I care for. nnHave you found anything to add to our collection?
Greetings. You stand in the Sentinel Mages Guildhall.  nnThis one is curious: what do you have there?
I believe Talia has finished  mixing the potion for your initiation. Speak to her when you are ready to begin the trial.nnMay Tu'whacca guide your path, initiate  always.
Welcome, wayfarer. Your exploits on the docks are known to me, but I know that your ways are not our ways. nnYou may sit and take rest in our hall, however, and partake of our services.
The sacred relics of Mara  are they safe? Have you got them?
The Stone Table. Quickly!
This business at the docks gets worse by the hour. If those shambling dungpiles come much farther up the beach we may have to do something about it.
Go. Exit  through the pit and help Indanas defeat the Hollow Lord.
Even if I can save some of these wounded, the Imperials will just kill them another time.

To Oblivion with kwama egg mining. I've worked out a deal with Shatasha to rent the ruins to the Mages Guild for research. nnIf that lost city is as big as she says it is, I should be well-off for quite a while.
We fought well, didn't we? I think we might just have a chance at turning this disaster into a successful operation.
You look much better now! Make sure to tell <<1>> old <<2>> took good care of you.
I should really attend to my patients. <<1>> can tell you what you need to know, if you can put up with his attitude.
You heard Sangur. Get going.nnI'm sure I'll be around when you return.
What happened?
Don't judge me. I had a moment of weakness. It won't happen a third time, I promise!
Next time I'm given a mission, you know I'll come looking for you. Be ready, my friend.
Ho there! Can't let you in here.
It's about time you got up. Father is about to give his big speech.
Oh, hey. Look, you really need to move on. I just need a break, that's all.
Is there anything I could get you? A drink? A little bit of my time?
Hey, thanks for the ale! Don't let me catch you around here again, or something.
Go on, use the portal and get out of here. We'll wait a few more moments for any stragglers that want to escape.
You seem determined to make yourself useful. What strange habits you mortals have.
You're a fool, and you've doomed another fool to unspeakable torment.nnIt's no longer my concern. I'll depart this world soon enough.
This war will kill us all, I feel it in my bones.
Do you have my ring?
It'll be tough going without the Captain. Command never really suited me.
You rescued me from a fate worse than death. I owe you, friend.
Welcome.
I have no idea why <<1>> would seal himself into that creature's tomb.nnBut I suppose he won't be around to undermine my experiments. Hmm!
You're a true hero.  Everyone in this company owes you their lives.
I didn't think we were going to make it.  Thank you.
There, you see? You fit in and no one will stop you from walking away. But, as this one said, there are opportunities here for people that fall from the sky.
You saved many lives today.  Azsu will remember you.
A shame the shrine is no longer kindled since the spirit departed. <<1>> will remain here for a little bit, in case the flame returns.
I hear you've done good work, recruit. Once we're off this island, I'll put your name in for a medal.
This conflict could have been avoided.
Speak of Namiira. Our specialist!nn<<1>> was just commenting on the difficulties pests present to any plantation. We'll be rid of these vermin in short order, yes? Of course, yes.

Oh! One more thingAndur scouted out the Orcs' Camp pretty extensively. He might have some useful observations if you ask.nnGood luck with the Wood Orcs  and that tricky treethane. Maybe we'll meet again when we find the Wilderking.
I really don't want to cover myself in this stuff.

You seem to be rather sharp, so I will not pretend that everything is all right.nnThe king is dealing with a crisis that threatens his hold on the throne. I would not bother him unless you are willing to help.
I'm still a little banged up, but we'll do our best to rally the troops and meet you upstairs.
Quite the view from up here, don't you think?nnIf only the company was equally enjoyable.

If this works, I'll owe the gods an apology. Fill the blood rune and then use it on the three seals.nnAfter that, we'll have to deal with the Binding Pool. Hopefully, I'll have figured this out by then. I'll meet you up at the gate to the pool.
Gone  father is gone. Why would <<1>> destroy his own family?nnPlease, leave me to my sorrow.
<<1>> knows you'll succeed.nnYou hear that, lazy senche? This one could replace the lot of you with <<cm:2>>!
It seems Akkhuz-ri may have hope here. Kazirra mentioned forgiveness, and perhaps helping to rebuild Arenthia will aid this one in atonement.
Well, that was more exciting than Tarrami anticipated!
I've never been more scared. I can't believe <<1>> wants to execute us.
I'm still shaking. <<1>> gave us the death penalty.
Leave me be. The loss of my brother is  difficult to bear.
Good luck and all that nonsense.
We're all so grateful to you for freeing us. We were in over our heads.
Nice to see Fort Rayles in Dominion hands. I feel safer already.
You were born under sign of the Lady, weren't you? I can always tell. Buy me a drink, gorgeous?
I should really go check on my father.
Thanks! I'm getting out of here!
I came here to get away from the war. But I see you and the Dominion have brought it to my doorstep.
Yes, yes, the Dominion has taken Fort Rayles. Makes no difference to me. You all track in the same amount of dirt.
This one rejoices that Fort Rayles is in Dominion hands. Honor to you for any part you played in this!
It's about time the Pact took Fort Rayles. Be nice to see new faces in town.
You must leave the moment you are ready. The Ansei Wards are gone and the Withered Hand has already taken to the desert winds. Go now and mete out the king's justice.
Speak to my fellow elders and state your case.nnWe will convene when you are done to discuss our options.
Good to see you here. With the Pact in Fort Rayles, I hope things settle down around here. I could use the rest.
Welcome! Saw some Pact soldiers heading toward Rayles. I hope to see a lot more Nord faces around here.

Well met, champion. Your deeds on the docks have done the city a service. You take a great risk in striking the Ra-Netu, but perhaps Tu'whacca's curse does not extend to outsiders. Bah! A matter for priests.
So, the Pact took over Fort Rayles. As long as no historical sites were ruined, I don't care who holds that place.
Now that Fort Rayles is in Pact hands, I hope I get some peace and quiet around here.
When is the Covenant going to take back Fort Rayles?
About time the Covenant started showing up. Fort Rayles needs to be retaken!
For the honor of the Covenant, Fort Rayles must be retaken!
For the honor of the Covenant, Fort Rayles must be retaken!
Why hasn't Fort Rayles been retaken? Has the Covenant no more swords?
A lapse in control leads to smugglers brewing skooma. If there's reason, I'll recommend Headwoman <<1>> shut this plantation down.
This one never thought you could best Tholbor, Zara, and Malarel. She is looking forward to ending your lucky streak.
I hear you're looking for some special substance. Some scuma?
Apparently my husband Farrokh does not know how to bar a door. We dare not go out while our ancestors still walk. nnI have asked Tu'whacca for intercession. All we have is prayer now.
