Walk with care. Tu'whacca's will has been defied at the docks, and his vengeance will be terrible indeed.
Thank ye, my friend. Ye let me see that preserving life is not worth abandoning it.
You did the right thing.
We're going to start over. We'll build a better life.
Once we control the portal, we can control the first section of the Chasm.
Erunor! I knew ye'd see. I knew ye'd understand.nnThank ye so much.
I wish I could go with you. I'm worried about my companions who've gone inside, but the priestess won't allow me to go in after them.
A magic force bubble? Really? nnThanks for getting my brother out of that mess.
Mara be praised! We truly cannot thank you enough for the return of these relics. Walk with Her blessing, feel Her smile on your face, and know always She will be with you.
How strange this feels! To be simply Zur again is  lonely.
I am grateful that you chose to save me. Still, I feel a bit lost. I wish  I wish Zur was still here.
If you can destroy the four focus stones, then we'll be able to control the portal and hold the first segment of the Chasm.
I'm ready to face anything, even the Dremora guarding this Chasm. But Akatosh preserve me, I have a profound fear of heights.
Make sure you destroy all four focus stones, or this war ends here and now. Our mages can't take control of the portal to the second tier while the stones are active.
The forbidden tomes cannot be allowed to cause more harm. Please, you must bring them to the shrine where they can be destroyed.
Move along, move along. I'd prefer if you didn't dawdle around here.
Move along, soldier. Keep this gate open for new arrivals.
Ah, you return to Zan! The siege range is yours to use, walker. Speak with Firamo or Miniel to refresh your memory of how siege weaponry works.
Covered my tracks. Couldn't have found me!
We came here hoping to establish a Dominion naval base, but our "forest of sails" turned into a graveyard.
May Jone and Jode watch over the town of Greenhill, and her people.
I never want to see another ship. I'll stay on this island for the rest of my life, if I have to! They can't force me to go back, can they?
You're going to think I'm wandering in my wits, but I could swear I just saw an Orc run through herewearing nothing but his underclothes!
You did an excellent job! Thanks to you, I was able to complete the ritual and end the vampiric threat once and for all.
May the Bright Moons light your path, Hallowed. You should know, there is an additional task you could undertake. It might improve your chances at Moonmont.
While this temple has been disturbed by outsiders, the light of Jone and Jode still shines down upon it. That cannot be said of all places on Khenarthi's Roost.

Only the dead and the desperate end up in this part of the desert. You are a Redguard, so I would think you know this  either way, you must be a very brave soul. nnDo you intend to enter the cursed grounds, the Tears of the Dishonored?
You're just  going to abandon me?
Whatever it is, it can wait. We need to get out of here!
Consult the mission boards for Grand Warlord Sorcalin's latest orders, soldier.
One may fear ghosts, but this one fears starvation more. Give but a little time, and a shop of such wonders will be set up!
I'm busy here. Don't waste my time, soldier.
You resemble a leaf in a tempest, unsure where to turn next. If you need training to find your path, I can help.
Welcome back. Use the siege weapons, if you need practice.
If you're skipping training, head out onto the battlefields and help the Covenant conquer Cyrodiil.
You seem in need of guidance. If you wish to know more of warfare in Cyrodiil, I can start you on the path.
Back again? Feel free to use the weapons or talk to the weapon masters. Just watch out for recruits firing weapons everywhere.
target: Gi tornato? Feel free to use the weapons or talk to the weapon masters. Just watch out for recruits firing weapons everywhere.

source: The Harvest Heart has been destroyed. My children are no longer slaves to Molag Bal!
So you are the walker who saved Laughing Moons! <<m:1>>, yes? How novel!nnTo think some consider them pests!
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
Are you ready for the next round?
<Talania Priscus has died.>
Thanks again for getting me out of that bubble of force. nnI don't suppose you're coming back to Bravil with us? I feel safer with you around.
Please! You've got to help me get out of here. I think I know the way, but I'm terrified of the crocs.
Thanks again, friend. nnI'm still seeing crocodiles behind every boulder. Brrr.
We're going to camp here until everyone is rested, and then we'll return to Bravil and the chapel.
To Moonmont then, yes? I will try to keep Khali from rushing headlong into danger until you arrive.
We shall see you at Moonmont, my Hallowed.
Please inform the mages that I'll be with them shortly. I know they'll be disappointed, but I need to have a few words with the Groundskeeper, first.
What have they done to my farm? Why would they do this? Animals!
I don't know if I can do what the Veiled Heritants want me to.
Comfortable? Then let's begin. Look deep into the embers as you listen to my voice.
This is not good news.
My homeland ablaze, and the guild split asunder. I never thought I'd live to see the day.
Unbelievable. To think  Ra'zaym was recruited into the guild by Colors herself. To sit here, hear what has been said .
Were it solely up to me, I'd have her head on a pike.
I bet things are going to get really interesting around here.
We'll contact you again soon, my friend. As soon as we have word of Sees-All-Colors. You can count on it.
When you have collected three gems, you may go to the top of the pyramid to complete the Trial of Spirit.
The statues at the top of this pyramid are dedicated to the challenges we face every day.
The statues dedicated to the challenges we face on a daily basis await you at the top of the pyramid.
I cannot believe she went through with it! nnAll I can say is thank Ruptga that I have other daughters. I will not even allow them to talk to Forebears!
You have begun your journey, pilgrim. Ahead lies danger. For now, you face only the light of the moons. Breathe deep of the moon-sugar vapors and open your minds to the Path.
I will gather an immediate accounting of events from those on duty. You had best give the news to the queen.
Ha! This'll make a real story, next time I'm drinking with the other Vinedusk. Thanks for the helping hand.
After he returns to Bramblebreach, Hazazi will request a transfer.
I'll make my way to the Hollow City after I've rested.
I think next I'm going to take my team and go do a nice safe dig on a beach in Auridon. Maybe we'll dig for, you know  clams!
Poke around the camp a bit more. Somebody must know what's eating at Gudarz.
Did I challenge you to a duel? I did, didn't I? Please accept my sincerest apology! nnI get a bit fiesty when I'm drinking mead.
What a timely arrival. You appear quite well-armed. My mages and I could have a great use for you.
You're the guy who helped killed those wolves! Thank you so much!
I don't know what I'm going to do with myself. Maybe I'll join Naerion's team, if she'll have me. Find someplace nice and quiet to dig. Don't know .
It's strange. In Coldharbour, my only thought was not of the Daedra, but what if I never saw Galandir again?
Ah, Tamriel! Fresh air, warmth, lower mortality rate; the whole package. I'm heading back to Firsthold, so visit me if you're in the area!
This "Selene" sounds like the ringleader for these Bosmer cowards. Before the day is done, I'll have her killed.nnI don't care what Carindon thinks he's researching.
The Bosmer will pay for what they did to the honored Patraud.

These Bosmer are feral, mindless. This "Selene" could be controlling them. There is a powerful blanket of magic covering everything in this forest.nnI'm glad our wits are still our own. I intend them to remain that way, if today is to be my last.
Two Mages dead and not a single forest spirit in sight.
There is a potent magical energy beyond this barrier of vines. Maybe it's Carindon's fabled spirit, maybe it's this "Selene." nnEither way, I'm not returning to the Guild hall empty-handed.
I'm not sure about this but Warlock Carindon seems to know what he is doing.
Two of my colleagues have returned to the Root so that the rest of us could stand here.nnI will honor their memories.
I finally got word from the dig near Falinesti
No way I'm going to let Uncle return those relics without me. I bled for this cause. I'm going to see it through.
Without the aid of the local tribes, our power here will remain weak. I hope the Bramblebreach will be but the first to join us.
Always good to see some fresh faces around here. You're welcome to go on in.
Those who honor the ancient Yokudan traditions are always welcome here.
Enjoy yourself in the castle. They do not like I there, so I stay down here.
Selene's menace has been neutralized. We are free to dissect and study her.nnI had thought the day lost, but this is exquisite.
By Tava's red feathers, these Crowns are foolish, arrogant, and intransigentbut it does my heart good to know that they are not all cold-blooded murderers.
Only in a town patroled by Crowns could this miserable business occur. nnIf our brother king exerted more pressure here, this tragedy might have been avoided.
A thousand deaths to the Withered Hand! nnTell our brothers and sisters to draw their long knives and ask Onsi's blessing. We Crowns have a new enemy.
I'm going to take Lorwen with us when we go to return the bones. I figure she has some blood in this now, right? I don't think she'd let me leave her behind, either.
Blessings of Tu'whacca be with you. Alas, we have much to do before meting out vengeance to the Withered Hand.
You look weary from the desert sun, and I sense you bear an added weight. nnWe Dunmer know about such things.
Necromancy in Bergama? As if we mages did not face enough distrust. Once again, magic must be  to blame. Terrible news.
<The ice construct before you moves with great difficulty. It notices your approach.>
Get out of here  it's not safe.
Please, leave me alone.
There are bandits I can feel them burning my island.
Welcome to the Vile Manse.nnDo you come to aid me?
By Onsi's bright blade! We don't see many warriors of your stature here in Bergama. Welcome to the guildhall.
Praise Alkoshthe Dominion controls every castle in Cyrodiil! The Warfront board currently has no missions. Consult the other boards for work to be done.

I give thanks to Ruptga for your intercession, wayfarer. Distrust between Crown and Forebear still runs canyon deep, but distrust is not hatred. nnYokuda lives in all of uswe must strive to remember it.

I heard the commotion out there, and somehow I knew it was you. I can't tell you how good it is to see you, my illustrious friend.nnAs you can see, we are in dire straits here, and it's on the verge of getting even worse.
<Upon examining this pot, you find nothing remarkable.>
Good to be alive today, yes? Fresh goods for you today!
These bags are made in far-off Auridon! What do you say?
Ah, so nice to see people of culture in charge of a city. What can I help you with?
Zetisha has cleaned house. Only Arenthia soldiers, Dominion allies under this roof!
What happened to us?
Did you find my lute? I feel almost naked without it.
We celebrate now, yes? Brew your own or try some of this one's!
We must feast, for we are alive! This one will help you.
We should give the students a moment to rest.
This one will meet you Skywatch. This one is not worried. He knows there's nothing we cannot handle.
So nice to be back under the eagle banner. What can I get for you?
Who are you? You don't look like a member of the Mages Guild.
This one is offering discount to everyone who fought on our side! She did not see you, but there is still much we can discuss.
I hope the Pact can be trusted to leave Cropsford, and Zenithar's shrine, unmolested.
Happy to buy, happy to sell.
It is good to see more faces from the Pact in Cropsford. Perhaps we will be safer now.
This one is supposed to tell you that she was neutral in this conflict. In truth? She is very grateful to be beneath the eagle banner again.
As long as you're not here to force me into the army, the Covenant's welcome to Drakelowe Keep.
Now that was some fighting! Managed to get out there and smash a few of the Colovians when no one was watching. Hah! Get you something?
The eagle banner flies again. Good.

The hour of our glory is nigh! Razum-dar forewarned me of your coming, and I have considered our circumstances carefully in light of that.nnI have the utmost faith in your capabilities, and I am confident that your arrival is an augur of our victory.
Time to do what we do best, yes? This should be fun.
They  they took my wife.
He'll be all right. We've suffered through worse.
This one is so grateful. Now Ahirunz can find the will to survive.nnIf it takes me an eternity, this one shall find a way to return to our children.
My Queen . I've failed you .
The <<1>> is just beyond this door, but it's barred from the other side. You need to go all the way around.
It's so good to see a familiar face in this dreadful wilderness. I appreciate that you climbed that tower to rescue me. nnA little longer and who knows what Drasilla would have made me do!
I just wanted to keep the dream alive. The dream of my Aldmeri Dominion .
Talk to Maluin. You will learn her terrible fate.
Ruptga's blessings be upon you, wayfarer. We Crowns move slowly and deliberatelyperhaps too slowly at times. Thank you for exposing that pawn of the Withered Hand.
Ahh, good to have our city back again. Damned too-talls, always looking down on us folk.
Thanks unto the Divines for bringing you to Bergama. Dihoq and I were a vulture's wing-beat from poisoning each other!
Well, the King certainly doesn't lack confidence. I can appreciate that. Might put our friend here in his place.nnThat'd be delightful to see.
Tu'whacca's breath, what a relief these kidnapings were solved. nnOf course, the Withered Hand is still out there, so I suppose I should dry my mouth lest I bring a curse on us.

If you happen to run into any of the workers out there, you tell them they better get their behinds back in here.nnI don't care if there are necromancers, zombies, or what  if they don't get back to work, I'm docking last week's pay!

Blasphemy! The Elder Scroll of Mnem has been stolen from our temple. I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but you will not feel their holy presence until our scroll returns. Perhaps you can help, once you complete your training.

As you can see, this is a horrible place. They just dump the bodies anywhere, and the predators, these harpies, come to feed on the corpses. nnMy Zariya  she does not deserve this. She has done nothing wrong!
Dumac take you, Covenant filthyou, these damn necromancers, and this whole damn desert!nnIf my sword arm weren't broken, I'd skin you like a netch!
I hope you find her. I don't know what I'll do if she's not in Vlastarus.
A draft of last year's census went missing just days ago. If my carelessness aided the Withered Hand with these murders  aiyah, I could swallow a sword.
I can't wait to see Eneriell again!
I've served the Magistrate for years. She's not capable of murder! nnThere must be some mistake. There must be.
Our Justice is innocent. He will not abide in those stocks for long, I swear it.
We've suspected the Magistrate for years. Embezzlement, paper-crime, and the like. nnEven so, I never would have thought her capable of this.
Please hurry. Angiente is not a patient man!
You see Fabanil, tell him not to bother showing up. I never want to see that fool's face again!
Comfortable? Then let's begin. Look deep into the embers as you listen to my voice.
I'll have a good life here, if you remain quiet about my gift.
Our Magistrate consorts with defilers of our dead? This is the ultimate betrayal. nnNeed you any more proof that Forebears are not fit to rule?
The Magistrate is the hand of our Forebear king, and she consorts with necromancers? nnFahara'jad's rule continues to bring nothing but ruin.
This talk of war  I thought we were done. We got Vanus back. Why can't we just go home?
Later, mate. I got me some killing to do.
So the Magistrate is to blame for all this kidnaping brouhaha? nnIn a town this brutish and rustic  one sympathizes.
Well? Did you find Klovag? Is he coming?
I have not the heart to look at the names of the dead. My son was so troubled. I had so much I wanted to tell him.
The Maormer are practically beasts. There are stories about them to make the fur stand on end!
I hear you've been helping the fleet recover from the storm. My family owns a shipping line, yet even I would be hard pressed to work so swiftly when the pressure is on. Bravo.
Well done. Our forces will take the sanctuary with little effort now. But we have another problem we could use your help with.
Sounds like you'll be having some fun of your own.
There were survivors? That's great news! I'm sure no one will mind a few dead miners once they see my trolls in action at the arena!
This one misses Kargand so much. He was always able to bring a smile to this Khajiit's face. His death has left a hole in this one's heart.
Long and long I have seen Sulma's sidelong glances, her nervous paper shuffling. This betrayal is not a surprise. nnSadly, I deem her replacement will be no better.
We get invaded, and everybody thinks it's a reason to slack. Not on Tohiba's watch!
Have you seen the Magistrate since her arrest? I suspect she won't live through the night.
Hurry up now! You were the one who said we did not have much time!
This one thinks he is doing better. The voices still speak to Kargand but this Khajiit can ignore them.
So Istah was telling the truth, huh? Don't matter to meso long as our customers stay alive long enough to pay their debts.
Hhmph. Raz is still angry you disobeyed him. But some of the moon priests here have been most informative about dealing with the circlet from Senalana. Some day, Raz may forgive you.
Sulma had no stone in her bones. If the Withered Hand wishes Bergama razed, let them come. By Onsi's bright blade, I will slay ten and ten before I fall.
Thank you for saving us! If you hadn't come along  well. I expect I'll wake up screaming for the next few years.
It is settled. We shall cross the Chasm and make our way to the planar vortex at the heart of Molag Bal's realm.nnNow that you know the plan, I have a special request to make of you.
With the Champions prepared, the Dominion itself begins to heal. We're going to make our way to Dune. The Two Moons Path awaits! I'll see you there, my friend.
Have to hire from Valenwood, find some new dupes to work the delve, and  excuse me! I'm very busy here!
I heard that the Magis  Magit  the, uh, Judge? She's been killing folks? That's a cryin' shame. Better tuck in another pint. Y'know, drowning sorrows  and such.
Good luck, Hallowed. I'm sure I'll see you again soon.
We shall see you at Dune, then. I look forward to our next conversation.
I look forward to speaking again at Dune, Hallowed. May the Green keep you safe as you do the work of the Bright Moons.

Damn shame about the Magistrate, eh? I heard she might even have been cutting deals with the Withered Hand. nnThe good news is that the next Magistrate might be even worse, so Samhudah's keeping me on the payroll. How's that for a happy ending?
Thank you for not slaughtering my people back in the forest.nnI've decided that I can no longer live like I was. I'm going to join you in your fight. I'm going to get back to Tamriel.
I don't know if I can go further. I'm afraid.
I heard a rumor the Magistrate was feeding the bodies of our departed friends to the risen dead. Tava's red feathers, I can't think of a worse fate than that.
I saw how annoyed she looked! Well done!
That fool has no idea of the danger you have put him in. I can sense the ghosts approaching even now. Tu'whacca forgive him  and you.

So it was the Magistrate who killed all those poor devils? She looks a bit waifish for that sort of work, but I suppose you never can tell. nnUncle Thakh won't be happy, at any rate. The dead rarely pay their debts.

You appeared to enjoy the power I gave you. I, too, know how exhilarating the power of death and darkness can be.nnAll this and more can be yours whenever you want it. If you join me in this campaign.
Did you recover the sword? We must speak before you go further with it.
I extend the claw of welcome, warrior.

Scourge take them! The Elder Scroll of Chim has been stolen! I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but you will not feel their holy presence until our scroll returns. Perhaps you can help, once you complete your training.
<A faint hum issues from the Aberrant Mathematics.>
I haven't seen my husband since the Dominion attacked. I wonder if he's all right.
I'm a fisherman, not a warrior! I can't take all this bloodshed.

As if we Forebears weren't hated enough, our Magistrate falls in with Tu'whacca's mortal enemy. nnI am thinking it is better to walk back to Sentinel with a broken sandal than to stay in Bergama much longer.

So the Magistrate was responsible for all this nonsense? My, my, my. What a dreadful development. nnI can't say that I'll miss the attention. Being an outsider while a murdering spree takes place is  unpleasant.
You look like you have something weighing heavy on your mind. Need a good drink to wash it away?
The faster you return with the blood, the faster you get your antidote. And trust me, it's not something you want to put off for too long.
Did you know this town has mead? They'll even feed it to dogs who ask nicely. Good choice, saving these people. Or whatever it is you did. You should've mentioned the mead before.
The hero of the cliffs returns in triumph! I do hope you didn't get too disheveled down there. Fighting alongside the peasants can be rather unpleasant. They really are disgusting creatures.

You descend a hole that only gets deeper and deeper.nnUnlike my opponents and I, you can still leave this place. Yet you linger, hoping that you can somehow save the mortals from the Mages Guild. How curious!
Go to Greenheart. Quickly. There is no time to delay.

And we find ourselves here once again  it's so unnatural. It makes me feel queasy.nnThe Eldest's heart must be the nexus that ties this plane to ours. I suspect it is also tethered to Naemon's Servantthe one who addressed us.

Did you hear? Ranneth wants to make me their town mage! Alanya loves it here. I think it's the mead. I can be a working spellcaster, instead of a failed student! I can do this! And it's all thanks to you. Thank you.
Goodbye now. It's time for me to rest.
Aranias tore open the ground below. You will find her and Andur in tunnels leading to my throne.
Go on. We need to do this before I lose my nerve.
Don't worry about me, I'll figure something out. I suspect this is not the last time we'll see each other.
You have my gratitude  and the esteem of the Eyes of the Queen. That is no small thing.
Our swords have prevailed! All Cyrodiil's forts are in Covenant hands. We have no Warfront missions now, but many others await your attention.
She waits for you atop this tower.nnShe is frightened of what is to come.
Marasadra just tends to the horses. Leave her be.
With <<1>> defeated we may just meet our recruitment quota.
Thank you, for everything. To kill someone in the name of the Pact, wronglyunthinkable! If you hadn't been here, this would have turned out much worse. Thank you.
New around here, aren't you? I advise you to have a talk with <<1>>.
The Elder Scroll of Alma Ruma has been stolen! I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but this temple is an empty shell until our scroll returns. Perhaps you can help, when your training is done.
After we talked through our little misunderstanding, Ranneth and I agreed that Pircalmo would make a good town mage. I quite like it here! The mead  so delicious!
With those bandits gone, we finally have enough supplies and equipment for the new recruits.
With those bandits driven out I can keep two eyes on the horizon and not worry about what's happening behind me.
In breaking the Shadows Watch, you saved many lives.

I knew Fahara'jad's appointee was to blame for this. It was only a matter of time before the Divines revealed her treachery. Onsi's blessings be upon our Justice Istah for finally bringing her to account.
Well, these Crowns are not quite as dour as I thought. Tears of Zeht, that wedding looks festive!
Make yourself comfortable, stranger. Everything the Manor of Revelry has to offer is yours for the taking.
Why do these things keep happening to me, I wonder?
You must be starving! Try everything. It's all so delicious. I promise, you've never tasted anything like the food we prepare here.
Our pools are warm and inviting. Feel free to take a nice, long soak.
Stibbons really wants to be a hero. Please help him so he doesn't get himself killed.
If you're here to join up with <<1>>, his day is over. nnAnd if you stick around, so is yours.
You're going to challenge <<1>>? Word of advice, run while you still got legs.
It just figures that <<1>> would get someone else to do his dirty work.
Why doesn't <<1>> just let us run off <<2>> and his militia rats?nnI'm tired of having to tiptoe around them and put up with their sneers.
What are you looking at?
It must be some madness blown in from the south. I wish I could clear my head.nnIt's like I can't remember something that I must!
This one's good-for-nothing brother Munyat sleeps all day, but Raban is happy to help you.
High Elf cooking? No, no. Too dry. Wood Elf cooking? Lacks sweet! You will find no better than <<1>>'s authentic Khajiiti cooking.
This one has traveled Tamriel to bring the finest arcana to you.
I generally find the Khajiit's grasp of knowledge lacking, but I'm impressed.
This one sees you have survived many battles. Buy my armor and survive many battles more, yes?
I hope you brought the key. We're ready to make the final push, but we're finished if we can't get inside.nnThis is our last chance to save our world. It's all or nothing now.
Close that reinforcement portal so that we can send the rest of our forces inside.nnI know you will make me proud!
So it's true then? You have retrieved my bow from the Shade?
Authentic Valenwood hides, certain to protect against Colovian arrows.
I wonder where that worthless boy got to. He should've been back with my herbs by now. Oh, pardon me.
Business is good, if you can keep the Bosmer from stealing everything in sight.
Yazhin complains about thieves, but he leaves his till unlocked.
Spotless woodcraft at fair pricessanded and polished to a mirror sheen.n nCome, look!
These damned cats'll give you tin when you ask for iron. Anything to save a drake. If you're here to do some real metalwork, I'm the orc you can trust.
The Khajiit have suffered much lately, but they are a lively people. They give hope to us all.
Daedra never sleep and neither do we.
The Fighters Guild will secure the line behind you. We won't give up any ground you gain us. Just get in there and open the way to the Labyrinth.
And here comes the great and marvelous Vanus Galerionright on schedule and just in time to take all the credit.nnI think he wants to talk to you.
Let the King know what you decided so we can get this assault underway already!
How odd. I never imagined my warriors would be pitted against the forces of Molag Bal.nnBut have no fear. We are ready to fight when you give the word.
Good drink makes good friends, yes?
She may not believe what we believe, at first. She is my superior within the clergy, and sometimes prideful. But she trusts in the moons. As I do.
It will take more than steel to keep the Colovians at bay.
This one has much to offer. From as far away as the Summerset Islesenchanting and mystical!
That worked? I mean, I knew that would work. Never doubted my calculations.nnUm, good job! The door ahead should be unlocked now.
The darkness is obviously designed to hinder our progress. An interesting conundrum, yes?
And another job performed to perfection by our champion. Well done!nnNow hurry through the open door and find the planar vortex. The end of the world isn't going to wait for you, you know.
His wounds  he's in terrible pain. We tried to heal him  but the damage  it's too extensive.
Well? I see you asking the rest of these daintyfoots for help, but you took your time getting to me.nnWhat am I? Too short for your precious army?
Your king must be informed. Let him know that we are ready to spill blood and defeat your enemies!
Has the time come to sail into the stormy sea? Do we pillage and plunder the domicile of the Lord of Brutality now?nnI'm eager to demonstarte the power of the Bone Crown!
A drunk Nord is worth a dozen of these sober milk-drinkers. Imagine how valuable a sober Nord can be.nnI haven't been in a good brawl in a long time. I'm looking forward to it!
Finally, vengance will be mine. I will make the Prince pay for what he has put me through.
Say the word and we will attack the Dark Father by your side.
We had to abandon everything when the Colovians attacked.
The Khajiit have been surprisingly friendly to us.
I think that Khajiit back there was interested in more than friendly conversation.
We need food if we are going to survive.
Where is Shiri? She should have been back days ago!nnI never should have taken that girl as an apprentice. Untrustworthy! There is something very sneaky about her.
Can you believe <<1>> agreed to join me?nnI've been a one-man act till now, but she's a bright lass and will make a great partner. And, she still holds the key for this chest.
I've been told that Shiri, the scholar's apprentice is on her way back to Bergama, but Scholar Zohreh says she hasn't seen the girl yet.
My fatherdoes he live?
That strange knight says the oddest things. But Vanus and the King seem to trust him, so what can you do?nnYou must be the champion that King Dynar said would lead us across the Chasm.

It is an honor to meet you. Prince Azah has told me of your deeds in Sentinel, and I know you have General Thoda's respect as well.nnWith you here, I think our chances of surviving this have improved tenfold.

May Y'ffre smile on you! You closed the rifts that bound us here! nnYou must stop that Shade though  it seeks to do terrible things to Valenwood. Though I have passed on many years gone now, I still consider Valenwood my home.
I can't believe we got caught up in all of that. I hope Pircalmo understands what it looked like. Thank you for showing up when you did.
I thought you were going to tell that matchmaker to let me off the hook. nnNon-bandits. You can't trust them.
Stop! I yield. I admit defeat.
Magic worries me. I can never quite trust all those mage-types. Maybe things will be different now that we have a town mage.
Get your lizard away from me, stranger!
You look lost
target: probably need some training. I can help you out.

source: The Green Lady is in Malabal Tor, but rumors of attacks from Redguards have reached us. It's imperative that the Green Lady be kept safe, so that she and the Silvenar may be joined.
This doesn't seem right. Sometimes I wonder if the Vinedusk Rangers understand things more than we do.
We'll talk again in Daggerfall. Look for the loud bunch in the back of the Rosy Lion tavern.nnAssuming you don't die in that cave, of course.
Sorry, friend. I have to get back to my companion.

Valenwood is only alive because of you. We are all in your debt, I especially, and having a Silvenar in your debt can be a good thing.nnI'll be on my way to Malabal Tor now. I will undoubtedly see you there.
Your loyalty to the crown will be rewarded, my friend. You have my word.nnGet in there and free the hostages and then we can go in and spill some Imperial blood.
Well played. I hope Zara wasn't watching. I was hoping she'd pick me to fight in the next division round.
I don't care to make this decision, but I must.
Hail, brother. nnWord has reached us that Talia now leads the tribe. Know that we stand ready to fight, should the shadow fall on Bergama.
Not all who come to train at Leki's Blade learn what they thought they might.
You dirty pig! Whatever you do to me, I will be avenged! You people were fools to even set foot upon Alik'r sands nnWait  you're not an Imperial, are you?
Whatever it is that you people seek to accomplish, your efforts will be to no avail .nnWait  you're no Imperial. Are you with King Fahara'jad's army?
Hail, brother. It is good that you have come. nnThe Withered Hand has been hereI can feel it. Stay vigilant.
No time to lose. Send any survivors this way and head to the inner gate!
By the gods, I swear that you infidels will all die. You will find that Redguards are not merciful .nnHold on  you're no Imperial  does this mean we're going to take the city back?
Be at ease. This is but a simple misunderstanding between merchants who bumped carts. No lives will be lost here.
You collaped the tunnel, the army's re-taken the city, and that son of a dog Khorshad is gone.nnThis ended far better than I hoped.
Thank you for exercising mercy on me.nnI do not believe the Imperials would be so forgiving, so I beseech you  you must slay them all.
This one  cannot speak. My dignity is injured.
The tribe will live and flourish in <<c:1>>. Be proud, you've given our people hope.
I should pray to Y'ffre before the meeting. Is there anything else you need?
Begone, outsider. You have no place here.
Still more tears to close. Very bad. Coldharbour is no good for living.
Once I finish stripping this one, I think I'll go in for a drink.
You're a new face to me, unlike that flappy buzzard over the barn.
I've been found! Oh, but you are neither harpy nor Gold Coast fiend. What a relief!
I have done as you asked, as I knew I must. Now leave me to my grief!nnPlease.
Keep one eye to the skies, friend. The harpies like to swoop down and grab whatever's light enough to carry. I've lost two hats and a goat to the feathered villains.
You're alive! I thought they might have taken you too .
There you are! Impressive work back there. The Maormer didn't know what hit them when our forces stormed inand I've got my ship back!
You ready to go? I don't know what the Sea Vipers plan, but I doubt we have much time to stop them.
If you wish my company, we should hurry. The Sea Vipers wouldn't commit their forces unless they're certain of success.
There are more Maormer sorcerers over there than I've ever seen, but I've been practicing. We'll find them all if that's what needs doing.nnMy power and yours, together. We can stop them.
Ah, great. The Eagles took over in Pa'alat. Now it's going to be just another boring tavern town under the Queen's thumb.
This Khajiit is glad to hear the Eagles have taken control in Pa'alat. There are too many dark things in the shadows to allow shadows to fester.
Look at this place! We'd better stick together and find a way to get to Molag Grunda and open the Gatehouse.nnI think Molag Grunda is barricaded within another room.
With the might of the Mages Guild on our side, perhaps we can finally push back Montclair's soldiers and take back Shornhelm's northern district!
Caution, friend. Not all in town wish the Dominion well.
As if this place weren't dangerous enough, now we've got foreign troops from Brindle in here. What are you going to do about that?
Good to see some faces from home. I feel safer with Castle Brindle in friendly hands.
With the Covenant in charge of Brindle, maybe I'll propose my idea for a wall around Vlastarus to the local commander.
Welcome to the tribe, sister. The wisdom of the Chief was deep as a well. I know his faith in you was deserved.
The Shadeyou must kill it if we are to end this.
I need to get away from these birds. With Brindle in friendly hands, maybe they need cooks. First meal would be chicken, if I have my way.
You draw the sword for us all, brother. True honor need  need not be named.  Avenge us.
So the Covenant took over Castle Brindle. Is that supposed to make me feel safer? Well, it doesn't.
The Altmer don't seem to think we're capable. Well, we'll show them who can fight!
The Queen and the Silvenar are safe as long as we are on watch.
You bear the tribe's burdens now, sister. Remembertrue honor need not be named. Seek not fame or glory, only justice.
Do not look upon me with pity, brother. Hearts such as ours, crowded with great and terrible purpose, have no room for such things.
Fill this poisoned cup with our enemies' blood, brother. All of the Alik'r watches you. May Tava speed your passage.
Word swirls through camp like a dust devil. So you are Ash'abah now? That is good, brother. nnTrue honor need not be named. Send the Withered Hand back to Oblivion.
Welcome to the tribe, brother. I regret we have nothing to give but our blessings.
Both Zamyad and Parvenah took to the Far Shores during your trial, brother. I fear we will lose even more swords yet.
If I ever find Donus, I'll return to Cheydinhal. I hope Kirandas hasn't given up hope.
True honor need not be named, brother. May your blade never go thirsty while these fiends still draw breath.
Vikord and I have a wager in play. Just to make things more interesting. Whoever collects the most Dremora hearts wins.
Sinfay thinks she can beat a Nord in a contest? Especially a killing contest? Ha! By the time we're through, I'll have more Dremora hearts than I can carry!

Hail, brother. The poison of Morwha's Bounty has run its course, thank Ruptga. It would take ten and ten to keep me from my work. Rumor swirls across the dunes. Some say there is a vampiric curse staining Leki's Blade, and now we have found proof.
True honor need not be named, brother. My son's sickness broke while you took on the crucible. You are indeed blessed by the Divines!
All praise to Ruptga: it appears my brother will recover. I take your arrival as a gift, brother. Divines willing, we shall fight beside you soon.
Well, well  took you long enough. Gran-gran could have cleared that cave out faster than you did. And she's only got one arm!
I think that little Wood Elf was planning to face Molag Grunda all by herself before Cadwell ran up there. You'd better catch up with them. I'll make sure nothing follows you.
Go speak to <<1>>. Perhaps she'll be able to help us.
You will help us find a way to forge these dangerous waters and get our troops past the Reaver Citadel. I have total confidence in you.
This looks pretty grim. We'll never find a way into that citadel. I think we should just cut our losses and head home now.
My brother's nervous. So am I. This quest of ours never seems to end!
There's bound to be a way into that place. I mean, besides the front door. I imagine there are a lot of Dremora waiting on the other side of the gate.
I'm impressed, little mortal. Hardly a scratch on you!
You did it again, my fearless friend! Well done!nnWith the Dremora caught between my powerful mages and King Dynar's relentless fighters, they won't know which way to turn.
Hurry, now. Get to the upper city and activate the Mages Guild portal.nnWithout the help of the mages, this entire endeavor could come crashing down around us.
You're back. Did you tell Brielus? Is he coming for me?
I hear you cleansed the blight. We're mighty grateful.
You've been such a great help! I'm off to see Telenger as soon as I finish this.
I'm exhausted. Find another sparring partner if you're still looking for a fight.
The ritual site is beyond the door. Keep that lodestone close at hand for those ritual horns!

Since both Alasan and Uwafa have been dealt with, the Withered Hand may be considerably weakened.nnPerhaps the third Ansei Ward is closer at hand than you realize. If the gods are with you, I believe you will recover it quickly.
Though the memories of Aranias fade, you areand forever will bea friend to the Valenwood  and a friend to me.
You have no idea how good this feels! To be whole again, and walk with my own two legs. To have legs at all!
You! You're alive! Just what I need!
Any time you're ready.
Thank you again for returning my brother's coin to me. I'll remember him whenever I feel it in my pocket.
I already told youI have no wish to suffer at the Taskmaster's hand!

I'd welcome you to Whisper Grove, but it's little more than a city of ash at the moment.nnPlease, I don't have time to take care of visitors. My husband Fingaenion here has been injured, and I have an army of Daedra to deal with.
Thank you for giving me closure. I hoped Divyth was still alive, but this is better than always wondering and worrying.
Stranger is good to this one, and to others. Now Khajiit has to do her part.
I'm going to have to figure out how to discretely return all of these things

You know where I stand. We have sliced through the enemies' ranks to get this far, and my blades are still at your disposal. nnI do not relish fighting, but I have trained since birth for this kind of thing.
I always hated my sister. But I'd never wanted her dead.
That pompous mage told me to keep an eye on her, and that's just what I'm doing. But I have the distinct feeling that I amuse her.nnI'm not sure how I feel about that.
I allowed your intrusion because it was obvious this would end in a clash of wills. It proved  enlightening.
I'd really like to be alone. I need to mourn my daughter.
I'm glad you brought the families some closure. Still, I would have liked to end the bastard myself.
You have this one's thanks, stranger. Moons' light be with you by night, always.
<<1>> is glad she could calm her brother down. He did not need to be poisoned by outrage. Your coming has not set all things right, but at least we still have our lives.
Shove something silver and pointy into their furry behinds, traveler. Make sure they know Atrius Axilla sent you!

Thank you, my friend. Prince Azah said you were indispensable. I now see why.nnYou do an old soldier a great favor by helping. I hope Shiri is not hurt, and even moreso, I hope that text has not been taken again by the Withered Hand.
Meet me in front of the cathedral when you are ready to launch the attack. Time is no longer on our side.

This is  unthinkable. Shiri came to me only a few months ago, but she seemed so dedicated. Of course she was! She was studying the Ansei Wards ! How could I not have seen this?nnI hope we find her before she does something  terrible.
Everyone says you've saved the village from committing a terrible mistake. Thank you, it will make my trading much easier.
Hey, thanks for setting us right.
So, you did it. Summoner Division Champion! It's an honor.nnNormally I'd offer my services as your servant, unfortunately Ishalga has reassigned me to other duties.
I understand congratulations are in order. Winning the Sorceror Division Championship is no small matter! Very impressive.
Won the Division Campionship for the Swordmasters, did you? That's damned impressive. I may place some coin on you for the finals.
Velyn Harbor is rumored to be overrun. I wish you luck. We'll be preparing for Malabal Tor ourselves.
You saved Greenshade and my people are safe. I can't thank you enough.
Is it true? What Cariel speaks? Indaenir, resurrected?
I wish you luck in Malabal Tor. I hope to see you at the joining of the Silvenar and the Green Lady.
It seems a ceremony is in order. Indaenir will meet up with the Green Lady and the two will be united in Silvenar. This one hopes to see you there.
Lord Gharesh-ri spoke of the ceremony between the Silvenar and the Green Lady. This one hopes to be there.
This one wonders where our journeys will take us next. Hopefully not back to Elsweyr so soon.
Sounds like the Dominion leaders will be moving to Malabal Tor. I'll remain to ensure the Heritance regrets setting foot on Greenshade.
A shame I missed out on all the fun. You owe me quite the tale now!

Believe me, I'd have been by your side, but  that Cariel. She's a feisty one. The things she threatened me with if I followed!nnI thought the Vinedusks were tough, but the Eyes of the Queen? I'll be happy to stay on their good side.
My guess is Indaenir's next destination will be Malabal Tor. I wonder if he's already met the Green Lady.
Looks like you took care of Naemon. Greenshade is safe now.
I hope our paths cross again under better circumstances.
This one hopes to see you again. Times are rough with Great War and we could use your help securing the Dominion.nnKauzanabi-jo only seeks to protect and educate the Lunar Champions.
You're going to duel Erthas, huh? Gilraen thinks he's been allied with the Daedra since long before Whisper Grove. nnI wonder if he still bleeds like a Bosmer.
So the word is you're going to put an end to Erthas. Good.nnI never liked him, even when he was one of us. Had a haughty air about him. Still, I never expected him to do all this!

Our powerthe power of the Ansei Wardswas compromised, and the Alik'r desert was in grave danger  but you stepped in.nnYou stopped the necromancers and the Alik'r desert is again safe from the risen dead.
You aided me at <<Ac:1>>. I'd be a fool not to return the favor. Whatever the Sea Vipers plan, we should hurry.
Now that the Imperials are gone, we can pick up the pieces. If the Divines will it, the Imperials will not come here under any other ill tiding.
Know, O wayfarer, how much we have lost. They may be gone but we may never recover.
I hope you slew every one of the Imperials you came across, wayfarer. It would only be fair if such woe would befall them as has us.
We're getting reports in from all over the desert. Withered Hand's crumbling fast.nnWe did it, my friend. We did it.
It has reached me that you had a hand in our liberation, wayfarer. Long may you prosper.
We have a new master nowhave you not heard? Such a sudden change.
I sense ill-doings in the cemetery, wayfarer. Our masters speak in hushed tones and Fadalia goes missing. I've no patience for such secrecy.
Do not tell anyone, but a sword-brother of mine has heard talk of vampires lurking in Leki's Blade.  Vampires! How could such creatures survive in so holy a place? It must be idle gossip.
The Cemetary is off limits to students now, but our groundskeepers remain outside. Odd.
The newly blessed swordsmen are just as quiet as the last. What secrets they tell at the graduation ceremony must be solemn indeed.
Since you won the challenge, I'm bound by our code to let you go. nnHowever, the other Ungodly might not be so scrupulous. I hope not, anyway.
Have you visited the graves of the Masters? We have been told to stay away, but It seems somehow easier to breath there now. I always gave it a wide berth before. The solemnity was  oppressive.
My soul lightens - a door has been opened, wayfarer.  I know not why, but Leki's Blade feels somehow holier since you arrived.
A new Master  ha. It is about time. Let us hope that they are marginally more competent than Fadalia was.
I'm joyful this has all ended, though I may never rest easily again. Beware of shifting sands, wayfarer.
Hark, wayfarer. Do you suppose the Imperials brought all of these boxes and barrels with them, through the tunnel you destroyed? I'm sure we didn't have this many.
DiscipleI mean, Master Raifais at least as skillful as Fadalia was. The school is in good hands.
Abide with me, wayfarer. Tu'whacca's breath, you've won us time for that, at least!
My relief knows no bounds, wayfarer but the damage they accomplished will be no mean feat to recover from. Zeht's tears, I may be fetching our things for ages!
I won't feign otherwise, wayfarer - it surprises me little that the coward Khorshad brought us to this. By my father's head, he never seemed entirely trustworthy to me.
I rejoice for we who yet live, wayfarer. My legs will never tire, now that we are rid of that menace!
By Tava's red feathers! Did you hear the rumor, wayfarer? Master Fadalia is a vampire! I will sleep with my twice-blessed silver blades close from now on.
The Imperials are like unto sand, wayfarer. As the wind brings them in, it avails us by carrying them away, just the same.
By Tava's red feathers! Did you hear the rumor, wayfarer? Master Fadalia is a vampire! I will sleep with my twice-blessed silver blades close from now on.
I was in the middle of my prayers when they forced me out of the cemetery. By Ruptga's starry breeches, what could be so important? Please don't tell them I was spying.
Though I know you'll presently be gone, wayfarer, Satakalaam welcomes you to abide as long as you need. Peace be upon you in all your dealings.
Zeht's tears, what are they doing in there? Master Fadalia's face was taut with concern. Did someone deface Ahtar's grave?
I had only just arrived to pray when Master Fadalia and the rest sent me away. I mean no disrespect to our teachers, but they might give us some warning next time.
Let's get inside and see what's waiting for us.
The school has gone quiet. Has something happened? I saw a small gathering outside the graves - some faces were flushed, others were pale.
We're as ready as we shall ever be.
I have never seen Nabeenam so silent. He has always been stoic, but this is different. It is something about Master Ahtar. Do you suppose someone might have defaced his grave?
I feel a fog has lifted since you arrived, wayfarer. That hidden dread flees and Master Fadalia goes missing. This no coincidence. We must remain vigilant.
By my father's head! The unworthy Imperials have made such a fine mess of things here.
Please, get rid of that creature. But be careful. Her magic is formidable!
So, many interesting sights to see, don't you think?
This one suggests you keep your eyes on your coin purse. The wood elves aren't to be trusted.
Shasirba makes such wonderful baked goods. You should try some yourself! Or, some supplies for the road from me?
Khuzi hopes you found that necklace well enough. She'd hate for someone so strong to be distraught.
I'm looking for a present for my sister but there are too many options.
I heard the Queen is in Rawl'kha. I hope I get to see her.
This one is very busy. Maybe another time.
Can you move please? You're blocking my view.
My brother did the right thing. That Altmer was a pompous ass.

We've been together in this battle since the beginning. You know I'll do whatever it takes to destroy the Withered Hand.nnThat said, Shiri's already proven more than a match for me. We have to win this one, and you know best how to do that.
I slave away in this hot kitchen but Duzal still buys meat pies from Shasirba. I need to learn her secret.
Seems we do more drinking than fighting sometimes, eh comrade?

I will join you, if you wish. nnI am no great warrior. I am only a humble priest, but Tu'whacca says I can be of great assistance to you in this battle. He says it is up to you to make this decision though.
Hush now, you'll frighten them. They don't know what awaits us! No one knows  no one knows .
Seems like just moments ago we were in Dune, yes? It is a good thing Raz is so quick on his feet. Wouldn't want you waiting on him  like we are waiting on the Guildmaster.
I don't know how you managed to pull this off, but the guilds are with you!
I heard <<1>>. Let's fight!
What do you want?
Your skull needs more dents. I can help you with that.
What are you looking at?
The Dremora are fully engaged. If you're going to get the Mages Guild portal working, the time to leave is now.
Once the mages get inside the upper city, the Dremora will be surrounded!
There may be some useful information in these old books, and this map is a remarkable discovery.
Greetings.
Now that my apprentice is back, we can finally get out of here!

This is a day I'll long remember! After months of searching I've finally discovered the location of my ancestral estate. It's not far from here! nnAs soon as I pack my things, I'm off to claim my rightful inheritance as the Heir of Direfrost Keep!
Not to worry, I'll be right behind you! We'll give that Valkynaz the thrashing he so richly deserves!
Hello, um, Maruin wishes to see you. He says you're late for your story.
I pray you can help me, good traveler. They have her, and I'm desperate!
Your choices were difficult, but you have made them well.
I can finally close my eyes.
Thank you again. The preparations for the wedding have been made, and so far, we have only been hit with tomatoes, and not rocks.

Good show! The portal belongs to us now! nnSir Darien and that lovely lizard have gone on ahead. I think he might be a bit intimidated by our prowess on the field of battle, and he's trying to compensate.
You've reminded me of my purpose. I'm sorry I ever forgot it. I hope Laurosse will forgive me.
What we did. Murdering an entire family. Is this what Y'ffre demands?
I'm glad they're dead. I don't care who hears me. Halalin  Halalin won't stop screaming in my head.
At last it is over. At last, I can grieve.
This one sees and knows what you have done here, walker. Your five-clawed assault will be remembered.
Fool that you are, this one is glad for you to have been here. A spotless choice, walker. We still have our temple and our city to keep, yes?
I have heard it said someone opened holes to Oblivion in the middle of Dune, and that a five-clawed walker had just the thing to plug up these holes. I wonder who could have done such a thing?

Great! I'm sure the Vinedusks there will appreciate the help, especially with the Mane hanging around.nnBodring is in charge there. Find him and let him know I sent you. That way he'll know I haven't forgotten him.
Dune will be sleek again, in time. Especially sleek if five-clawed walkers like yourself fill its streets, this one is thinking.

No army has come, and yet Dune stands free of daedra. Shimsamu has heard a strange walker, sleek and five-clawed, is to thank for this. Do you think this walker might be available? Or if this walker had any siblings, that would be fine too.
The Sea Vipers are insane! They're trying to create another hurricane!

Magundim watched you fight, when he could. To have learned it all is impossible to expect, but I think I learned enough to be able to help my city. Perhaps a future with the guard is in store for Magundim, yes?

Dular wonders, walker, if you recall whether certain buildings were intact during your foray into Dune's merchant district. It is best if they all are, of course, but for this reason and that reason, it is better for me ifNo, I go too far.
Those bastards killed Patraud, for little more than stepping into the clearing. These Bosmer are savages.

The danger is gone, yes? Can you tell me, walker? If it is safe to walk into the city once more, Yanu-ma has many bellies to fill, she thinks. Perhaps you would like some of what Yanu-ma has to offer, hmm?

This one hears the claws that came to unravel Dune's knot bore an uncanny resemblance to the one standing here, now, speaking to him. If that is so, this one thanks you,  but reminds you, not everything can be free after a disaster.
I'm flattered by the attention, but I think it's time you were on your way.

Anyone capable of what you've accomplished here should consider membership in the Guild. We could use someone like you.nnEspecially since you've proven yourself capable of tackling daedra and dark anchors.
Closing a portal system of that magnitude is no mean feat, even with our assistance. You should consider joining the Guild - we could use someone like you.
Isn't it amazing? The crisis has ended, but our little town will continue. I'm so pleased!
I think I'll keep the tavern open. This safe haven needs to be preserved.
I've decided to stick around. Help turn the Hollow City back into a proper city. Who cares if it just happens to be in the middle of Coldharbour? That just adds a bit of character to the place.
Well, I guess I'm stuck here. Someone has to help feed all these people.nnJust my luck, the Hollow City has become a destination spot.
This guild hall is certainly more impressive than many of the posts I've been assigned to. And it feels good to have fighters running around its corridors.
Even far from everything we know, some things remain the same. Potential mages guild candidates, carrying a strange tome or two, picked up on your travels. Care to show me what you have found?
Thank you for your intercession, wayfarer. Between the harpies and the Gold Coasterswell, I might have had to sell this place.
Thank you for muzzling those mercenaries, wayfarer. As with all dogs, a thump on the snout is sometimes required.
I would've liked a few harpy heads mounted on the tavern wall, but at least I can let my horses graze without me guarding them.
By Tava's red feathers, it is well to have a moment's peace unmarred by harpy screeching. I do not know how you did it, wayfarer, but you have my thanks.
Long and long have we suffered under those sellswords, O wayfarer. Would that you had killed them all. Only then would we be truly safe.
Mulama is ruined! The harpies leave and now the dungy Redguard buy no bows! nnYou will buy something to ease this one's sorrow, yes?

No more sound of fighting comes from our Dune. The sight that this one sees is that of our Dune's guards and soldiers and people moving about. She is thinking perhaps the walkers of Dune thirst for Moon-Draughts' moon draughts.

Ah, the five-clawed walker! Four-Toes is thinking of writing tonight. Could you tell him if you said anything witty, perhaps, while fighting the invaders of Dune? This is important, it is for posterity.nAs always, I am ready to trade, as well.
Well, well, if it isn't the hero of the Pact. Glad you made it.
Hi, can I help you?

It's good to hear that the harpies have settled, but my blood still boils at the sight of those mercenaries. They'll not have any of my steel as long as I draw breath. nnYou, however, are invited to look over my goods.
It is as this one thought! None could stand up to his flashing blades, no. None tried, but the result would be the same!
At last, those harpies are gone! I can't wait to start working on some new outerwear. nnYou look eager to begin as well. Can I interest you in any of my goods?
The harpies are gone, but for how long?
Tu'whacca bless you, O wayfarer. At last I can sleep without fear of the sound of wings.
At last, the village returns to normal. Now we can attend to the vital business of removing Andrin from office.
I had hoped you would burn the harpies out, but I suppose bringing those mercenaries to heel is some comfort.
The harpies may be gone, but their tangled nests and foul droppings remain. We have much work left to do.
Zur has found you! This one is so happy now.
Peace with the harpies? May as well make peace with the scorpions and fire beetles as well. nnBetter a thousand deaths than to share water with those winged horrors.
I'm grateful for what you've done, O wayfarer. My inn is still in shambles, but at least we can rebuild without fear of further disaster.
Blood and glory, friend. I would have liked to thump some of those harpies with you, but duty calls.
Brave meeting, friend. Good job accounting for those good-for-nothing sellswords. I heard them howling through a stone wall.
Welcome to the Kozanset Fighters Guildhall, traveler. nnYou look capableeven dangerous. Have you considered joining the guild?
I can't wait to watch what the Daedra do to you when they finally catch you. I just hope I'm there to see it.
It was good of you to protect the town as you did. nnI still wish we'd used our powers to help, by Y'ffre.
Greetings, seeker, and welcome to the Kozanset Mages Guild Hall. I trust you made it here unmolested? The Redguards are not overfond of our presence here.nnI am curious: what do you have there?
You again? I knew you were up to no good! Get away from me before I call the guards!
Are you still here? Perhaps you should pull up a rock and help us with our work. Do something useful while you're here.
This one wonders, why are you still here? Don't you have a great mage to rescue or something?
You're going to leave me all alone again, aren't you Alexis?nnWell, I forgive you anyway and I'll be right here when you return.
Aldolin cannot be far. If you find him before we do, be wary. He will not yield to you and must be put down like the cur that he is.
About time you got here.
You'll want to talk to Copper, not me. My word has a hefty price.
Excellent. Manthir often peddles his wares here, but right now he is likely at his home just across the market to the east. Look for him there to start.nnAnd don't worry, Manthir is a soft one.
If you want to talk to her, I won't stop you. She lives in the next house over.
Please inform my colleagues that I'll be with them shortly. I wish to finish speaking to the one who calls himself the Groundskeeper.
I can't wait to get back into uniform. Undercover work isn't my cup of tea.

You are the one who killed my brother Uwafa, are you not?nnI will grant that you are likely a formidable foe, but once I become a lich, I will burn you to cinders. There's nothing you can do to stop me now.
Thank you. We were on our way to Longhaven when the Argonians struck. Free my companions and meet us there. I'll repay you however I can.
Come see me when you are done with the siege weapons, warrior.
You have done well, traveler. Stand beside Shazah, struggling against the darkness. You have taken your first steps down a difficult path.

All clear? Good. I'll be stationed here indefinitely, for the security of the Dominion, but it's good to know things are safe for now.nnI wonder if I could get that Khajiit girl to bring me a snack every once in a while.
All this skulking around, using up valuable energy on apprentice-level illusions. I grow ever more weary. Even Zur's enthusiasm is ebbing.

Y'ffre's bones, I've been seeing flocks of cats scurrying about Dune since the fighting stopped!nnDo cats flock? Or is it a "pride" thing? Could you ask one of the khajiit that?nnAnd if you do, come back and show me the scars.
Don't waste time searching for me after you leave. You'll have larger concerns soon enough.
A Daedra attack! My, my, my. A nasty business that. At least they left my gems intact  mostly.nnGet you something?
Steer clear of us Armigers. I don't think your reputation could take it, hero.
Don't mind Craw, she likes messing with people. You seem like you could use a bow. Do you want to go hunting some time?
You again. I always seem to run into you right before I do something I'll probably regret.
It will take time to accept what you have said.nnI This body is so heavy.
Nidras, a thief? And to think I trusted him with our valuables! How embarrassing.
It must be done and I would be most grateful.nnYou should know that who or whatever wrote this book bound it to the labyrinth. To traverse one, you need the other.
Ah, you're back. You have the meat pies, yes?

Azdanten has heard of a skooma distillery, that it has been destroyed, that it was in a cave under an old blind walker's well.nnOf course, you know Azdanten has had nothing to do with that nonsense. This one is an honest trader, as you well know.
Excuse this one, walker, but her curiosity overcomes her, and she must know! This one hears stories of ghosts, and that they have been exorcised from a local home.nnWhat is to be made of it?

I've been hearing stories of bandits in the area!nnOur caravan has only two guards for the moment, do you suppose they will be enough?nnSome of the khajiit have been saying the bandits have been dealt with, though. I guess it might not be a problem.
I overheard something a bit absurd from some of the locals.nnThis town had a local crime lord? The thought is honestly a bit ridiculous.nnI can relax a bit, I guess. That's always good news.
Been hearing interesting things, about someone meeting your description dealing with a local ring of bandits, smugglers, drug runners and the like.nnNice work.
Now I have to wait for him to summon up the courage to approach me. I wonder how long I'll be waiting this time?
Ever lasting darkness awaits. Nothing bad could happen.nnOr Zur is a horrible liar and this is not good at all.
Wait till I tell Mother the news. The rest of her hair will fall out!

The Sea Hawk is just there, on the southern dock. Remember, the silks are likely below deck. And while I know Angore is not aboard, I can't guarantee that his goons won't try to stop you. You look like you can handle yourself though.

Good work! Hostages came out and we attacked. Cut right through the bastards and scoured the city. Just a handful of Imperials holding out now.nnI still haven't figured out how they got here though  I'm worried reinforcements may be on the way.

You must hurry. Sooner or later, the Lord of Schemes will become aware that we're closer to our goal than his army realizes.nnI'll keep this portal open for as long as I can. That should allow us to bring in a few reinforcements of our own.
I would not enter the mine now for love or gold. There's not enough of either to convince me.
Please, come, browse my wares! I have many fine drinks and brews. Available to one and all!
Have a look! Take all the time you need. And spare me your wary glances! Colovians like myself have a rich history of trade. Really, we do.
You have performed better than I expected, even in the face of unrelenting danger and the worst horrors Oblivion has to offer.nnI am impressed.
Speak to your friends, for these moments may be their last. nnBut do not tarry too long. Time is fleeting, and each moment is a thief that steals far more than it brings.
What are you doing here? Why aren't you saving my daughter?
Thank you. May the Green keep you safe in your travels.
<A wooden ring on the corpse's decaying hand indicates this must be Zariya. <<1>> may want the ring as a keepsake of his wife.>
Yenadar's grace be upon you. And Kala's prayers go with you as well.
Ah, Nirnroot wine, nectar fit for the gods. As long as they can afford my prices that is!
Woodhearth welcomes you with open arms and warm embrace.
Split-Tongue hears Rakhad no longer hides under the rocks of S'ren-ja.nnThis is good news for Split-Tongue, for his tongue was split by Rakhad's minions. It is a small kind of revenge for him, yes?
There are unscrupulous shopkeepers in Woodhearth, but Adaishir is not one of them.
Silly Bosmer. We pluck the wealth from the Valenwood and sell it back to them, and they pay us joyfully.

This one hears all sorts of good news this day!nnAbout this thing and that thing, this friend has a pregnant mate, that friend met someone new in Rawl'kha, and best of all - that stink of skooma is all gone from this one's town!nnA good day, yes?

So I found out while those skooma slingers were running out of town that, when they lick their teeth, it's one of those little signs of skooma use.nnI had no idea.nnShould I just not say anything, or should I tell someone it's okay to want to eat me?
Bury an axe in that Daedric bastard!
This one hopes the Claw will remain safe now, walker.nnWhat an end to a pilgrimage, yes? Stillthe Claw is safe. This is what matters, this one thinks.
Molag Bal has much to answer for. Remember those who gave their lives today.
I wish I could go with you. I've always wanted to cut down some Daedra on Molag Bal's home turf. But I have confidence you'll get the job done. Good luck.
This one hopes your hands ran red with the blood of the Stonefire.nnEither way, you have done the Order of the Claw such a service.
The Claw is safe, yes? nnMoons watch over you in your travels. Clearly you have their blessing.
Leave me alone. I don't want to hear anything you have to say.nnYou've ruined me. How could someone like you come out on top?

It's you! I remember you! You've filled my pockets! I'll buy you a drink, but you're not exactly my type, ha!nnWhat's the matter, not funny? Malacath's bloody teat, a killer like you should laugh more, ha!

Wealth beyond measure, muthsera. Someday  perhaps, someday, I will be ready to meet you in combat. But I have seen that this is not a fate yet for which I am prepared.nnYou are like a saint of strife in the arena, muthsera.
Well, plough me sideways. The dung-breathed child won a fight or two.nnPat yourself on the back, my hands are busy and you're not worth the sweat of my pits.

Hey, it's my victorious friend! We are friends, right? Damned fine fight!nnThey're letting me change divisions! Did you talk to anyone? What did you say about me? You didn't call me a coward, did you? Hah, of course not.

Nonsense. Clearly you're sleeping with the judges. Or you've poisoned the water supply or laced your weapons with filthor some other trick.nnYou're no better than me. You can't be any better than me. It just wouldn't be fair or right.
Keep your head. Clearly I'd lose my arms trying to take it, heh.nnI'd rather keep my arms and rejoin the One than lose them to you. It's a hard thing, to lick a stump so close to your face.

Oh, hello. I think we've met, haven't we?nnDid you just win something? Are you a fighter? That's very interesting.nnI think I've earned enough to make my way back to Wayrest. There's something important waiting for me there, but I can't recall what.
Why do you bother Mazou-dar? You have your earnings.nnYou already know you cannot bet, walker. Be happy with your money and go.nnWhy talk to Mazou-dar? He has nothing for you.
Well fought, sera. Well fought, indeed.nnDid I bet on you? I'll never say, but ask yourselfdo I seem upset? Go on. You've more fights in you, I think.
The spirits spoke of you. Thank you for helping our village. We will provide what support we can to your cause.
I saw bright lights up by the tower. There was something spectactular going on up there. nnNo one believes me but I think it was a battle!
I saw you training a new kind of guardian. Magnificent!
Ah, you ran off without your reward. Here.
The Dominion demands armor, and I provide it. Strongest in Valenwood.
Spare nothing. Waste nothing. The flesh, the hide, the bone: the Green provides.
Say what you will about the Thalmor, they know fine cloth when they see it.
The Thalmor have requisitioned much of his stock, but Puzhbar-jo will provide what he can.
I'm not interested in handling lizards myself. All I care about is the final result of the race.
The new management sounds harsh. Why don't you ease the transition a bit for me? It won't take much, just a few coins.

It seems the merchant with whom I am meeting has been slain, sera. Such a pity. This  dungheap  has been an excellent source of workers for House Telvanni.nnSoon, my partner and I will be recalling to Tel Branora to find other such places.
It'll be good to go home!
One thing will never change about Leki's Blade, no matter who the master is. We will still need to read stacks of books every day.

Own no weakness or fault, sera. The caravan's master is dead.nnI couldn't be happier. These n'wah slave-merchants always keep such dire, filthy markets. House Telvanni may often be within the ash, but these conditions? Unacceptable to us, always.
By Mauloch! It seems like this dungheap is starting to empty out. Fine by me, these toothless runts were starting to get under my skin.nnWant one for the road?
It is a relief to hear that the Caravan is under new management, yes? In celebration, why not buy something?

Oh, five-clawed khajiit, you are sleek indeed. When next you and this one are in Dune, if you wish for a fine meal and fine company, she will be your host.nnCount on that, five-clawed walker. This one had no expectations of you, and you impressed.

Are you the one they sent to aid our cause? Go right on through. This passage will take you to the sanctuary. Major Cirenwe is waiting with further orders. We'll hold this side of the passage to ensure no trouble comes from behind.
I admit I was worried about my cousin, but you have settled the question as to her fate. I'll miss <<1>>, but at least I know what happened to her.
Wolf hide, deer stomach, rucksacks for every occasion.
Make a decision, will you? Mannimarco could return at any moment!
So Sendel saw your worth. She has always been wise. It is good to have you on our side in this.
Luala left for training at Tu'Whacca's throne when she was very young. I hope she will agree to see to our plight.
These lands are so lush and green.nnAre you looking to trade?
It's so wonderfully warm. A fine day for a bit of trade.
I'm not that bad, tell her I'm not. I can get better.
There are so many dead now. I hope that Luala can bring the Thronekeepers here from Tu'Whacca's Throne.
I have many fine wares for sale and trade.
I will set out for Tava's Blessing as soon as my wounds are set. Thank you for seeking me out.
I'm very glad I was able to find you. Otherwise, my search has yielded nothing. nnFrom here, I will journey to the city of Kozanset. Perhaps there are signs of the Withered Hand there.
Come see me when you are done with the siege weapons, warrior.
Thank you for coming, wayfarer. I'm glad you are here.

Well, this has my knickers in a twist! We have a perfectly fine army, but what good is it? Sitting around this side of the Chasm, twiddling its collective thumbs.nnIt's rather embarrassing, if truth be told.
Yes, yes, I am far from home. I tired of the smoke and ash of Morrowind and yearned for something new. Now, are you wanting to trade or not?
Welcome back, warrior. If you have questions about Transitus Shrines, ask.
I'm glad that the Imperial has found someone else to talk to. His haughtiness is suffocating.
Oh, thank Y'ffre. I wasn't sure I would find anyone out here. My village needs help. The forest has turned against us!
Astanya can pass word to Her Majesty. Perhaps you can catch a ride on the Prowler. Raz heard Jimila plans to set sail. He suspects she may owe you a favor.
<<1>> is dead, and <<2>> must soon follow. Their fates are tied, you know. For what is a body without the spirit?

Whoever lived here before had a splendid eye for decor. This will suit me just fine.nnWe spend so much time worrying about what happens after life when we should be embracing death and the powers that come with it.

The choice of decor was not my own, if that's what you're wondering.nnIt would appear that this city had its own worshippers of death. I guess even Meridia did not know everything that went on under her very nose.

The colors in here are so drab. Why did the Groundskeeper send me here? My station requires better accommodations than this!nnI can't wait until I'm back home in the Altmer lands. I need to see beautiful colors again.
Rabiza always has the best prices.
The time of battle is fast approaching.nnI should have never let myself get comfortable again. Sometimes it's easy to forget that outside these walls, death waits for all of us.
Please, a coin for my family? We lost everything in the storm, surely you can spare a coin!

Even though it was a trap, I wish I had had more time to explore the library. Imagine the treasures and knowledge I could have acquired!nnAt least Kireth managed to grab a couple of books before we left. I can't wait to start reading them!
It's good to have Raynor back here with me. I  I don't know what I'd do without him.nnJust to see him examining maps and thinking up his next device. It makes me really appreciate how far we've come.
Oh, when I find that Stibbons, he  he will hear an earful from me!nnHow dare he think he can just vanish and leave me all alone? I'll  he'll  he'll be punished severely for this. Quite severely.

For all the years I've spent researching and looking into just how the planes of Oblivion work, I still find my self astonished at every new discovery.nnThat library for instanceI've never experienced a spell quite like that before.
I hear you've been busy, my friend. Good. Very good. nnIs that letter for me?
The treethane is just inside. He'll be glad to see you.
We're holding them back, but I took a few hits. Just give me a few minutes to catch my breath.
I can't tell you how glad I am you're here. Something is horribly amiss, and we can't leave this cave without fearing for our lives until it's put right.
I'm sorry for what I did. Isn't it possible to look the other way? Isn't it possible to forgive?
So Treethane Rolon wants you to investigate the violation of the Green Pact. I don't see what there is to investigate. The culprit is plain enough, but I'm happy to help.
Advocate, please take the convicted to the judgment chamber. The Green will decide the fate of the guilty.
It's amazing how similar everything is despite all this time. I suppose there's only so much you can do with hide, bone, and stone.
You have done what we could notyou have restored us to the Green Pact. All is right, even if all is not yet well. Thank you.
Speak with me when you are done with the siege weapons, warrior.
I've been apprised of some concerning news regarding the Maormer operations off the coast.nnWe appreciate your efforts, of course. We must also remain focused on the tasks at hand.
Welcome, adept. Mind your step here.
Welcome back, comrade. What news from the field?
Hello, adept. Having a fair day, I hope.
Welcome back, comrade! What's the news?
What is it now?

I'm positively chuffed things have gone so well! To be completely honest, I didn't think we had a ghost of a chance. But then, if we weren't up against overwhelming odds, we wouldn't be heroes, would we?
Aha! I caught you red-handed, Artisan! Thieves just can't help returning to the scene of the crime.
With my heraldic cane back I can show myself in court again. You have my deepest thanks.
Castaril is sleeping peacefully now that you've returned Pluck's pelt. He uses it as a blanket, you know.
Thank you for finding my drinking horn. Cassirion and I drank from it at our wedding. He has forgotten, but I drink to remember.
Everything is here. Wonderful. Allow me a moment to apply our elixir .
Come to stare at a dying Nord, eh? Hate to disappoint you. None of it's fatal.
The Bishop and Gharesh-ri are already clammoring for my time, my friend. I'm sure we will see each other again. You are the Hallowed, after all.
Who are you? What, you want to chat? Thought this day couldn't get any stranger.

Are you collecting junk for Adamir's little monsters? Good, good.nnI make little monsters too. See this? It's a ant-fly-worm beast. I mashed them together and added a pinch of Adamir's life juice. It's an adorably gross little guy, isn't it?
You again? Sorry, I have all the ash I need. Good day!
Nirnroot wine flows again, thanks to you. May the Divines ease your path, wherever you travel!

You are a sight for hollow eyes. Those harpys were going to tear me apart.nnBut this isn't over yet. The Roost Mother is just up ahead, and she wields more strength than anyone you've faced so far. Only the Captain himself eclipses her.
You're <<1>>'s friend, right?
You made it! I was beginning to have my doubts, but I trust that the vicereeve will no longer be a threat?
Sounds like we won't need these barricades much longer.
Heard you ran into trouble in <<c:1>>. Sounds like you cleaned up whatever mess the Argonians left.
I haven't seen tracking like that since Haras was leader of the Hounds.
Legend in the Hounds is that there was a Wood Elf named Haras who was the best tracker that ever was. I think you might be in competition for the title now.
You don't understand. He's insane! He'll keep trying to control the undead until he succeeds.
Why did you let <<1>> talk you into this? Do you know how much trouble he's brought to <<Ac:2>>?nnMy apologies, his very presence wears at my manners. What do you need?
The captain wants all these supplies catalogued and stowed before we contact the Thalmor. I should really handle this until <<1>> recovers.
