If you think you can help us, talk to Treethane Rolon. He is our leader and handles all matters of justice.
Thank you for returning my censer, but I don't know if I want it anymore. There's too many sad memories associated with it now.
Listen, we don't need any more trouble than we already have. But if you want to help, talk to Treethane Rolon.
There's some trouble up ahead. I thought I would let you know.
I once heard Ledronor talking about a great tracker named Haras, from a long time ago. If I didn't know better, I'd think you were him.

This is Brackenleaf's forest you're entering. Pick no fights and respect the shrines and you're welcome to stay as long as you like.nnOtherwise, you'll learn quick enough why they call us Brackenleaf's Briars.
You have the blessinggood.nnThen with open arms, I welcome you to our family, Brackenleaf's Briars. May you succeed in all your hunts and the great tree keep you in the shade of his leafy branches.
What was it like to fight Master Pellingare's children? Don't tell my boss, but I never liked them.
You're the one who defeated that army down here before, right? We're looking for someone, and could really use your expertise.
You! You're the one who killed my children! You whoreson dog! How dare you show your face here againI. nnHaven't you done enough to my family?

Feel free to return. Soon, I'll have this place looking as grand as it ever did.nnAll will be welcome. The locals  perhaps even witches, if they'll look to reform. Drodda claimed that witches are not evil. We'll see.

Brackenleaf is pleased, but you are not finished yet. Each hunter is also prey to another hunter. Wolf hunts tiger and tiger hunts snake and snake hunts wolf.nnIt's not enough to hunt your prey. You must also prove stronger than those who hunt you.
Your trial is not complete until you enter my trunk and reach my heart. Are you ready to enter?
We have no quarrel with you, living one. Indeed, we thank you for your part in awakening us. The invaders in the Barrowbough must be stopped!
Survived then, have you? Jolly good, jolly good.

I may not like her, but your Dremora friend has certainly been good to her word. She used her own blood to open the door for us. I've never seen anything like it.nnWell, off with you! And remember, we'll be right behind you.
The darkness is obviously designed to hinder our progress. What an interesting conundrum.
Finally, vengance will be mine. I will make the Prince pay for what he has put me through.
Fate brought you to us at this turning point. I'm glad to heed your advice. We must cling to life wherever we find it. You reminded me of that, and I thank you.
Thank you for convincing Erunor to return with us. Thank you so much.
That mage keeps popping up in the strangest places. I'm not sure I trust him. He thinks his boots don't stink, if you take my meaning.nnAnyway, I believe he'd like a word with you.
You're trying to go to Coldharbour? I wish I could go with you. I heard there's islands floating in thin air!
The truth is a bitter pill to swallow. Now go. I don't want to speak about this any more.
Do not hasten towards this final hour. Take the time to appreciate the things you have, the friends you have made, and the world that birthed you.
We'll be by your side for the final battle. In the meantime, we'll prepare ourselves and keep the Amulet of Kings safe.
You needn't make the choice now, but when the hour comes, know that we will stand with you and accept your decision.
I'm not going to tell you to put it out of mind. One of these people is going to have to die for you. Can you make that choice, when the time comes?nnOr will you fail, to the doom of us all?
Farewell, my brave brother. I will never forget you  and the sacrifice you made for our people.

Magister Wulfdis didn't believe me. He said he was going to have me expelled from the guild if you didn't show up. I'm sure glad you did. nnI just hope he doesn't send me out on another impossible assignment.
Good to see you, sera! The Tribual Priests have been kind enough to open their home to us in our time of need. Try not to break anything.
Hmm. This one smells some magic on you. Do you not sense it? Maybe Magrus licks your face while you sleep! Ha! nnWhat is it that you carry?
Praise Vivec! We now possess the six Elder Scrolls. Soon all of Cyrodiil will be ours!
Why, Sameer? Why? You have broken the most sacred tradition of the kingdom!  nnNothing can justify such sacrilege. The law is clear, Sameer. Exile. You must leave here now and never return.
Go now. Lord Varen awaits.
I've run these johads since I was a young man. Damned if I'll see them fall to another!
I welcome you to my father's home. Please excuse our scant hospitality. I've been tending to Naseiran day and night, and it leaves little time to prepare for guests.nnHow may I aid you?
Good to see you, comrade. Hope you've had ample opportunity to batter around someone deserving.
Welcome, comrade. Help yourself to whatever you need.
Welcome, comrade. A pleasure to share your company again.
What is it, comrade? Make it quick.
Welcome, comrade. The Guild prospers with members like yourself.
Whoever paid off the workers wanted the johads to be out of commission. Sounds like the family has some enemies.
Ahh, it's my comrade in arms! Welcome back to the hall!
I suppose I will have to advance Anenya to the rank of Journeyman now. nnGods help us. I hope I don't come to regret this.
Hello hello, comrade! Good to see you!
I'm through being a victim. When my leg heals, I'm heading north, to join the Covenant. Black Daggers won't touch me then.

I feel a measure of peace. I did as much as I could to help my town and the people of Rivenspire.nnReezal-Jul was empowering that abomination. Making it stronger. We would not have been able to stop it without your help. I am grateful.
This one would ask if you have found Saifa, but Zaddo sees it in your eyes. Walk your path well.
The moons speak to Saifa. They tell her of your journey, the ceremony, the choice, and the fire.
You'll make the difference here. I've been out in the field for a while now. You get a sense about these things.
We've never had such a thing happen, coming back to battle against Orcs. I'm not the only one eager to leave right away.
Have you seen my father Nedaegar? He's been missing ever since the Orcs attacked.
Now is not the time for us to speak. Listen to the words of Glaras.
Now is not the time for us to speak. Listen to the words of Glaras.
Now is not the time for us to speak. Listen to the words of Glaras.
Your training nears its end. Now to tell you how we capture the enemy's forts and resources.
I'll feel better knowing I didn't leave the mayor of Crestshade completely on her own.nnRemember, head into town and look for the mayor's house.

We are ready to leave poor Crestshade.  nnWe worry that some touch of the abomination might remain within the items we used to lure and destroy the creature. Bury them here, and let them be forgotten.

I don't know what you did, but the shades are a bit sluggish. We'll hold off the dig until they return to the ground  if they return.nnI should send word back to the Mages Guild. They'll want to know everything.
I'll stay here and warn travelers away from <<Ac:1>>. Don't worry about me, I'll be all right.
What's wrong? What did Varen say?
This <<1>> business is deplorable, so close to <<2>>. No doubt the Mages Guild will take the blame for it all!
You look perplexed. What inscrutable riddles is Varen spouting now?
Sai Sahan wishes to speak with you, Vestige. Be brief. He needs to rest.
I wonder where I should go? What to see? What to do, who to meet?nnIt's a little scary, now that I can do it. But I'll figure something out.
The sooner we can get out of this place, the better. I can't take much more of this kind of magical nonsense.
I didn't cut Sanguine Alendil, but I did make a potion from its flowers. I accept the judgment against me.
Will Uta-Tei return to the Hist, or the graht-oaks of her new forest god?nnAh. Such discussions are better with a drink in hand.
I would never violate the Green Pact. I have lived by it all my life, it is unthinkable.
Activate the portal in this chamber so that the rest of the troops can join us.
Before we left our home, we thought no good could ever come from Elves.nnSometimes it's best to be proven wrong.

I'm not entirely sure what happened, but half of us are dead and we seem to be talking to the Dominion.nnAt least all of the tension that's built up seems to be gone. I have a peaceful feeling from this. We will see what happens, it seems.

I-I remember now. I remember it all! Oh gods! What accursed thing did I do? The spellit trapped me in the tree's form!nnIt was a nightmare! Such was the price of my lust for longevity. But now  now I am released?
Not so much arguing anymore. Lots of my friends gone, though.nnThat makes me sad.
We have crushed our enemies! All Cyrodiil's keeps belong to the Pact. Consult the other boards for tasks, as we have no Warfront missions now.

You've done well. Permit me to tell you a secret, behind which hides another: Any true Shadowscale is also a true child of the Hist.nnThe Hist provides a measure of eternity, true as it also shapes the minds of our people. Think upon this.
Thank you for returning my journal to me. It pains me to think that it ended up in the wrong hands.
This is not how this should have happened  but the Thalmor have said we can stay.nnTime will tell if they come with whip and brand. Then we will know how right Slim-Jah was.
The Argonians are innocent of murderous habits, I hear. Good. May we leave this mire to them and move on. nnIf you need anything from our supplies, do let me know.
The cursed axe worked even better than I expected!
This is even better than I hoped! Think of all the fringe benefits! I don't need to worry about food, water, or even the heat anymore!nnBut most important, I still get to be with my sweet Musi!
May the Light shine upon you as you enter the heart of darkness.
Lieutenant Fairfax needs those healing supplies. A lot of our soldiers were wounded in the surprise attack.
<There is nothing more to be done for him now except to search for his companions and possibly inform his order of their fate.>
You wished me to remain in my home, and I will. But my servants cannot distinguish you from an intruder.nnGo  take the portal to the relic thieves, and do not trouble us further.
Hmm. Perhaps if I tweak the mixture
<Ragged breathing is the only sound coming from this Bosmer.>
It's time, isn't it?nnI'm ready for anything! I can't wait to see what's inside the lair of a Daedric Prince. Is that what he calls it? His lair? Yes, that sounds right!
An entire room plunged into darkness that we have to cross. Nothing suspicious about this at all.nnLuckily, I have just the plan.
This trial has been hard on all of us. Please help us find closure, advocate.
Your evidence was indisputable, advocate, but it's still hard to believe. Hurry to the judgment cave. The sooner this is resolved, the better.
Forgive Sai Sahan for his anger. Ultimately it was Lyris's decision, and her sacrifice to make. He'll come to realize that, eventually.
We did it. Tamriel will go on. But what a terrible price we had to pay.
So, this is where our roads diverge.
Are you insane? Don't stop to chat with me, get up there!
It's almost over. There is just one more thing to do. The convicted must be brought to the judgment chamber.
Five-claw! Adusa is glad to see you again, my friend!
Lead on, then. Take me where you will.
You got one of them, but what about the rest? You have to keep digging! Find the full truth!
<The Elf doesn't appear to have any other items of value.>
<The book describes how to summon and communicate spirits of the dead.>
I'm not surprised at all by how this turned out.
Oh, a fellow member of the guild. Well met. I'm here searching for a few others of our order. I don't suppose you've crossed paths with them, hm?
Any last words for the prisoner?
Well met! I'm glad to see you survived the battle of Northpoint relatively unscathed. We're going to need you to finish this.nnProvided we ever get started.

Mortal, you stand above the sealed ruins of <<1>>. Within is a gateway to <<2>>, where my priestess <<3>> suffers at the hands of Molag Bal. Her pain is so great, it has torn a hole between worlds.nnThis injustice must end.
Greetings, outsider. As the will of my Prince is eternal, I heed your call.
That was  exhilarating! Nothing like a near-death experience to get Adusa's blood flowing!
I was waiting for Adusa when something hit me from behind.
Keep  keep back! I'll cut  I'll cut you!
I never thought I'd be happy to see bloodfiends. I think we're back in our world!nnWith any luck, the switch works and we can open the final door.
Ah, by the look on your face, Adusa assumes you were successful? The vampire commander is dead, yes?
I've fulfilled my part of the bargain. Gwannas is no more.
<The sapling does not stir. Its leaves are shriveled and wilted. It looks quite dead.>

Well. How fascinating. It will end a lot of controversy back in Orsinium. nnFunny how quick every clan is to claim credit for the work of a gang of bandits. Everyone wants to know who will get the glory.
I heard Gargak is dead. You didn't happen to bring his head back, did you? We could mount it on our walls, here.nnIt'd be fitting.
If you find the flowers, leave them. I just want the dirt that held them.
Heard Gargak's dead. Good. Still feels like there's a snake in my guts.nnDoesn't feel good, by the way. In case you were wondering, feels pretty bad.
Gargak's dead? That was you? He wasn't so strong after all.
Gargak had a chance to redeem himself in Malacath's eyes after the dual dishonor of failure and poison, but he died.nnSounds about right.
gargak dead
gargak dead
gargak dead
gargak dead
gargak dead
Razum-dar was quite adamant that he wanted to see you as soon as possible. nnI would prefer not to delay you any longer.
Well, I guess things are settled. Gargak dead, we can get back to our mine and our affairs.nnSpeaking of affairs, I'm an armorsmith. If that's your kind of thing, let's talk.
Queen Ayrenn awaits you at Hectahame. Hurry to her aid.
Shakul and I have forged many weapons to defend ourselves. With Gargak dead, we won't need them all for the stronghold.
If Gargak won the duel, our stronghold wouldn't be so weak.nnI'm drinking to his memory. Join me, if you've got the coin.
Better to end Gargak's rabble, I suppose. Need anything?
With Gargak dead, things can get back to normal. Hungry? No poison, I swear.
I do not know you. Why are you here? Who sent you?
Marcel trusts Balcone. I don't.nnBe careful, <<1>>.
Adusa wishes she could go with you, but Verandis has other tasks for this one to perform.
Leave me to my suffering! It is only compounded by you standing around gawking like a child.

I was wondering if you were going to make it. I hired one of these little boats to ferry me down the Bay. Whatever it takes to get as far away from that trolls' den as possible.nnIt's expensive, but I have the coin to spare now.
If you and Adusa hadn't shown up, we all would have fallen to those monsters.
I made sure we got out of Moira's Hope without incident. Well, the Khajiit helped. A little. But I wouldn't make a big deal about it.
Comrade, you've done it. I am free. Free from Ragnthar's barrier, and that dark cat's shackles.
Stop. I must alert the mayor to all new arrivals.
Forgive me for not getting up. It's been a long day, and I'm ravenous.nnIs there something you need? Are you new too?
I thought for sure we were done with all this. I followed the others through the portal, and now look what I've gotten involved with! This looks like the end of the world!
Did I hear that right? We're going to blow the vortex apart?nnGreat! But how do we get out of here once the light explodes? Please tell me you have an idea!
If we had known this was happening, maybe my people could have stopped it. Valenwood is part of Nirn, after all.nnBut that's probably just wishful thinking.
Are you sure we need to destroy these chains? They add a nice flare to this otherwise dismal setting. Oh very well, let's get to it!
Always be thinking before speaking. An audience enlightened may not be the right audience.
Please! At least make sure they let me loose when the battle starts! I can help fight!
The people eye the north with fearful eyes, but it's from the south that the storm approaches.
All Sentinel will be thrilled at the return of the Memory Stone. It is a sacred relic, you know?nnI will tell the king your name so he will know who did this.
I'd fight with you again any day!
Did you really just talk to that crow? You must be drunker than I am !
Death needs time to grow what it kills.
The Divines saw fit to send you and your friend to save us, but how could they allow something like this to happen in the first place?
Funny boat, funny business. I want to see what's in the hold too.
Moramat has told me what you've already done for us, outlander, but I have to ask is it done? Is Gargak dead?
Mark the men who would turn this city Imperial. Signal my black-feathered followers to strike. The rest on you lies.
Be careful out there. The bloodfiends are pretty mindless and easy enough to put down, but those vampires are cunning and fast.nnAnd then there are the bats. I hate bats.
Give the Captain my regards!
Pray that your decision to save my  sister  wasn't a mistake. I shall look to Arkay for tolerance, but I'm not sure I'll ever accept that this vampire is really Janeve.
So your journey begins. I wish you safe travels. Let our blessing aid you on your path.
<<1>> barred all entry from the cathedral.nnSorry, orders.
The scouts you rescued brought reinforcements from <<1>>. We subdued the townsfolk for their own protection.nnTell me, what happened in the cathedral?

It seems <<1>> held up his end of the deal. I felt his  absence, I should likely say. I was able to open a portal here without any difficulty.nnI tried to tell <<2>> what happened, but he wouldn't listen.
Thanks for saving my hide. They were trying to find a big enough pot to boil me!

And that's why you're my new favorite mortal. When you kill something wonderful, you keep it interesting. Fresh! Dare I say, jovial?nnMakes me wonder if I should stick around, see what wonderful things you'll kill next.
What are you doing here? I don't know you.
It's not fair! I never wanted this, any of this, and now I'm to die for it!nnBut you're reasonable, aren't you? We can talk about this, work something out?

Ah, there you are! The Groundskeeper said you had a pickup. I assume she was talking about this merry band?nnGood to see them alive and well. They are alive  right? Not that I mind the odd zombie. It's the smell I can't abide. Nasty, that.
Do you need directions, hero? The ruins are in the Lorkrata Hills, northeast of Shornhelm, just beyond Traitor's Tor.nnNow get moving. Verandis will meet you there.

And so we've come full circle. I led the original Five Companions on a quest to reclaim the Amulet of Kings. At the time, I told myself it was for the good of all Tamriel. nnI was wrong and now all the world suffers for my hubris.
Zeht's tears, I thought I could handle this! Mannimarco's sorcery brought back all of the pain and doubt I felt inside the Halls of Torment.
You better keep an eye on me. I'm getting ready to punch Tharn again.
Welcome back! Please pardon the mess.
Have you satisfied your contract? There are fewer Black Daggers to plague us?
I trust you have fulfilled the contract on the Black Daggers.
Well? Here to tell me of piles of Black Dagger corpses left in your wake?
I understand your anger, Vestige, but I hope you will give me the opportunity to make reparations for my transgressions. My intentions are honorable, I promise you.
Varen and I have work to do, but you and I will talk again very soon.
I saw that vampire in action. He's extremely deadly. You're going to have a real battle on your hands when you get up to the house.
You pulled me from the pits of Oblivion. I owe you a debt of honor, small one. And a Titanborn pays her debts.
When the time comes, I will call upon you once more.nnI won't advise you to travel safelyI know you too well. But keep your wits about you, and learn.
My sister-in-law is feeling a little better. She's almost back to her old self and talking up a storm. Thanks to you.
I'll stay with Sai and Kasura. Get the ring back to the Harborage. We'll meet you there as soon as we can.
We've done it. We have the ring, and we're one step closer to recovering the Amulet of Kings. We might just pull this off.

The shades seem to have weakened, but that hasn't stopped them from probing this camp.nnDoesn't matter how long it takes, we'll keep the mages safe so they can get back to their dig. Orders are orders.
I was beginning to wonder if I'd ever see you again. Any news?
Truly you do the Eight's work. Thank you.
You do Eight's work, traveler. Thank you!
We're asking these two to give up their lives, but one of them has to do it.nnRemember - they did this to themselves.
We'll find Sai Sahan, and if Mannimarco gets in our way, I'll chop that sniveling knife-eared puddle of troll piss into little bite-sized pieces.
Sergeant Antieve's at the west gate, by the bridge to Stormhaven.
Sai Sahan served me well for many long years. It saddens me to think of the tortures he endures, but I'm heartened to know that he has not been broken.
Thank you.
Thank you.nnI've lost track of the days. I feel so hollow.
I'll feel better knowing someone went to check on the mayor of Crestshade.nnRemember, head north and look for the mayor's house. That's probably where you'll find her.
Keep you wits about you and your weapon handy, for many dangers surround Camp Tamrith.nnWhen you reach the camp, find Captain Janeve as soon as you can.
Give me a few moments to catch my breath and I'll be back on my feet in no time.

Did I overhear correctly? Fahara'jad asked you to go to Evermore? nnSounds like that place is shaping up to be a real trouble spot. I wish I could come along, but the guild's got me doing something else. Probably not nearly so interesting.
I, for one, am very glad Fahara'jad sent you. Many here in Evermore believe the rest of the Covenant has forgotten us.
The attack was sudden and terrible. I don't know what the world is coming to.nnThey didn't steal anything, though, and I still need to make a living. So feel free to browse my wares.
You can't believe how tired I am of getting attacked and chased by those Eight-cursed monsters!nnI just want to go somewhere safe.
Etienne is dead? And,  Squire Theo says the healer is at fault, and dead.nnIt is not truly justice, but it is done.
I'm told there's a dead witch somewhere in the village. Good.nnIt's what witches deserve, when this is what they bring.
I've heard about what happened. All of this death all around us, and you killed her, a skilled healer, too. I'll never understand war.
That huge witchman was the Zurric woman's son? Stendarr's Mercy, at least he's dead.nnDo you suppose she was some sort of spy? Or did she think she was protecting her home?
What a mess. This whole affair  We should just go, put all this death behind us.
Well, good! Now to clear them all out. All of them, from everywhere.

So I heard you killed her son in front of her, then Squire Theo cut her down.nnThat's pretty cold. Be glad she wasn't an orc, she would've torn Squire Theo's arms off and carved her son's name in your chest.
Medya Zurric delivered my brother's children. She was a good woman and you killed her.nnBut my house is still on fire. I guess I don't know what to think anymore.

Medya Zurric was a witch? Well I'm glad she's dead, her and her witchman son! If there were three more of her I'd want them all dead!nnLook at my home! Just look at it! She deserves everything she got, I tell you. All of it.
It seems everywhere I land, you turn up. Or is it the other way around?
Can you believe we're standing in King Fahara'jad's palace? You may have to pinch me.
What do we have here? A legend among heroes! You're looking good.
My friend! How good to see you here. Have a drink with us! Help us celebrate!nnTelonil worked his magic. We have our own ship. We're a crew again. Soon, we'll be back on the sea.
Once again, well met. I hope you are enjoying the warm air of Sentinel. I find it quite bracing, myself.
My friend! My friend. Oh, it is good to see you. I have had the most horrid month.
I hate my life.
The wind and the water smile upon you, my friend. I had not expected visitors. What brings you once again to the Spearhead?
This one greets you, five-clawed walker. Your reputation grows.
Hey, look who it is. I see you're still kicking. I'm glad, but I'm also jealous.nnJust for once, I'd like to leave the boat.
Welcome to the Sisters of the Sand! Enjoy your stay, and let me know if you need anything.
All these clothes. All this jewelry. Whatever is a poor Bosmer to do?

She's gone. Lakana. She was the bravest of us. She was our hope.nnI've heard only rumors surrounding her demise. I don't know who cut her down. But mark me, friend  if I find him, he'll suffer a lengthy death.

Have you come to pay your respects? If so, I thank you. I am glad to see you here.nnNo man should lose his daughter, least of all a king. It is a sad day for Sentinel, but Lakana lives on. She lives now in our hearts.
Hey, good-looking.
At last. We're finally going to explore a real set of ruins, just Neramo and Clanker and me, and Clanker doesn't take a split.nnI'm so looking forward to this.
What an interesting collection of tomes.
You did it. You always do. You have my thanks.
That woman is incredible. She saved my life.
Sentinel. I never thought I'd see it. The world is full of wonders, and thanks to you, I'm seeing them one by one.nnToday, I'm going exploring!
I've never been to a market like this. It's so  quaint. Redguards are remarkably polite, considering the war.nnYou did well on the docks. Quite well indeed.
My friend! Welcome. I want to introduce you to my wife.
I thought my husband was lost. I mourned. Now he is returned to me, and he has told me everything.nnYou have given me back my life and his. Words cannot express my gratitude. Walk with Tall Papa.
Is there a reason you're poking around inside my house? 'Cause I can poke back if I have to.
Thank you for speaking to us, young one.nnWe need to speak among ourselves now. The story you tell is quite  disturbing. Now we must decide if it's true.
As promised, I will consider what you've told me.nnMy thanks to you for bringing this to our attention.
You have spoken. I have listened.nnNow we are finished here. Move along.
I must say it is good to see Queen Arzhela back upon the throne. Hopefully those filthy Reach barbarians won't cut her reign short.
Ah, I have seen you before! Were you not the one who drove the Ra-Netu from Sentinel? nnYes, it is you! A thousand thousand thanks, my friend!

You seem very confused, and I am terribly sorry for that, but I'm not lying to youI've never seen you before.nnI hate to be rude, but if this this is the book, would you mind letting me take it back to the Mages Guild?
Queen Arzhela will make a fine ruler  perhaps better, even, than her late husband.
So the duke was fouling his nest right under my tusks. By Mauloch, I knew something smelled rotten. nnI won't let it happen again. Trust me.
Thank the Eight our queen has returned. nnIt's a small miracle she didn't die of exposure in that drafty old chapel.
The people celebrate now that our absentee queen has retaken the throne.nnUnfortunately, joy won't fill an empty stomach or rebuild a home.

Once <<1>> is secured at the <<2>> Mages Guild, I hope to aid <<3>> in locating her Walking City.nnTo think, I came here to visit a friend. Yet I leave with a great purpose. Does all adventure have such a strange beginning?
So you found those dirty Orcs in Torog's Spite, eh? Good on you, chum. nnNow about these other allegations  I swear I never touched that horse!
Perhaps I shouldn't have used Stibbons' blood . He must have gotten caught in the spell somehow. Ah well, I'm sure I can figure out a way to undo it eventually.
Impressive  for an outsider.
Well, look at what the wolf dragged in. I certainly wasn't expecting to see you again so soon.nnOf course, you're always welcome here, as far as I'm concerned.
Without <<1>>, the soldiers have released us from service. We may continue our pilgrimage.
So the Imperials want this city? I say let them have it. We can all amble away while they're still busy raking up the bird droppings. Auri-El knows that'll take an army.
Thank the Eight I can see the sun again. nnI'll never look at those birds the same way, though.
Anisha is depressed. All the tasty crows have flown away. Now she must go back to eating bland dungy porridge.
Thank the Eightour long black feathery nightmare is over. Now we can go back to complaining about the gulls.
Captain Hjurrun's just around the wall there at the south gate.nnI wish I could be there to see the look on his face when you bring him that head. It's gonna be great!
By the Three, our rights and duties. Welcome, comrade. I trust your blade has a few new notches in it?
Welcome to the Evermore Guild Hall, comrade. nnThe thrice-cursed Daedra continue to grow in power. You must have the best arms and armor if you are to defeat them.
Hail, comrade. If you happen to slay a daedroth, give it a good kick from me! I'm still nursing a bite wound from my last outing.
Ha har! What's this? Another big-footed pup come up for training? Tell Larhoth all about it.

We can dispense with the small talk. I know why you're here. Even in the nature realm, news travels fast among crows.nnGetting to Uela is impossible though. Even if you break her wards, entering her domain will corrupt your soul.
Don't mind the dustI'm just doing a bit of sorting. nnI understand you're a member in good standing. Would you care to look over my wares?
Hmm  I sense you've come to the Mages Guildhall for a reason. What have you got there?
I had a feeling that was going to end in bloodI didn't know it would be like that, though!nnI feel bad for my guildmates.
My next personal project  I'm going to figure out how to open two portals at once.
You come seeking knowledge, yes? The Mages Guildhall is the place for you!
If you hear anything of Falinesti in your travels, please send word to <<1>>. I expect I'll be traveling with him for quite some time.nnAfter all, I am quite adept at driving off the frost trolls.
You're new, aren't you? I saw you leaving the guest house.nnAnything I can do to ease your transition?
Maybe with this Imperial nonsense taken care of we can get some decent provisions. I was maybe one day away from eating my cat.
Thanks for your help. Make sure you tell my cousin that I'm all right. If you head south, you won't be able to miss the Serk.nnTell her I'll be recruiting new members for the Maulborn in no time!
I was so relieved to get that letter from my cousin. Between knowing that he's all right and performing these good works as a member of the Maulborn, I feel like I'm on top of the world!
Welcome to the Marbruk Mages Guild. We recently established this branch, so we're always looking for new members.
Welcome to the Woodhearth Mages Guild. Are you interested in uncovering the forgotten lore of Tamriel?
I'm no fan of the Empire, but if they can wipe out the Reach clans and send me back to my farm  I don't know. Maybe the duke was right.
It is good that you revealed the duke's treachery, wayfarer. It is unclear what became of him, however. Were we in the Alik'r, his punishment would be both public and brutal. nnI miss the desert.
I hardly thought Queen Arzhela had the strength to preside over a meal, let alone an entire state. I tell you thoughI've never been so happy to be wrong.
Staying in the guest house, are you? I'm sure your induction will go smoothly. Most of them do.
Ah! You're staying with us? How nice! If <<1>> can help you in any way .
You're new here. Watch yourself, running about and bothering folks. We don't take kindly to nosy people.
I'll recover. Just find the intruders and make them pay!
Greetings, guildmate. It is good to see you still among the living. Take some hard-earned rest or resupplyour battle is far from over.
Well now, that is a relief! To think I might have lived out the rest of my days that way.
Ah, I was told that I might encounter you hereabouts! You do not know of me, but I know of you.
I hear we may be able to return home soon. Is it too much to hope?
Greetings, comrade!
You are the one who brought back Horseman Rolan's sons. I've been eager to meet you.
As always, you're welcome to rest and reequip yourself.nnDon't tarry too long, thoughthere's plenty of killing to be done!
So many things to do! Adusa doesn't have enough hours in the day.nnPerhaps you could lend a hand, my friend. You help Adusa, yes?
Leave me alone. I'm only here for the wine.
I'm just trying to have a quiet drink.
Can't you just leave a man to his drinks?
What can I do for you?
The Mad Architect waits below.
You must defeat Uela. Only then can we be free.
You've had quite the glimpse into our world. A bit more then Wyress Freyda or myself would ever be comfortable with, but luckily, for all our sakes, you've proven yourself trustworthy.
Sahan doesn't look well at all. Keep an eye on him.

Oh, it's you. So I guess I didn't really mean what I said about taking your legs off. I mean, you'd get mine first, ha!nnChampions must be busy people, fighting all the time. So, go on and fight! And fight often!
No need to alarm yourself, friend. This is merely an illusion, and all part of the treethane's plan. nnSpeak to Fariel. She'll explain everything.
We've heard a lot about you, Queen's Eye. Have a word with Fariel. She's been waiting for you to arrive.
Thank you for all you've done here. Today has given me a lot to reflect on.
You found them both and returned safely. Thanks to you, I still have a sister.
Stendarr must be in a giving mood today.
I know the Evermore soldiers will appreciate any help I can get. Last I heard, they were spread thin.nnAs for me, I may just take the long way around into Evermore.
I hear we're to be allies with the city dwellers now. I suppose if it saves our home, it's for a good cause. Especially with the added bonus of ridding ourselves of the Reachmen.

I'll caution youdon't expect a warm welcome from my sisters in the north. nnThey are not accustomed to city-dwellers in the wilds, but they need all the help they can get. Whatever it takes to rid these lands of that Hagraven.
This alliance is foreign to us. I think we're all concerned about working together, but at least our common enemy is worth it.
I pray the Wyrd can help me. I don't know what the Reachmen did to me, but this darkness they speak of . It's as if I can feel it. I've never been so scared.
That must be why Elgenie's poultice didn't fully heal me. I wasn't conscious for a while after they captured me. He had time to  to .nnIs what Wyress Delphique says true?
What brings you to my husband's grave? I don't think we ever met.
Did Countess Tamrith give you a poultice for me? I could use a little something to dull this pain.
We meet again, ally of the Viridian Sentinel. Now you seek to subjugate these woods once again. We will see if you can succeed.
What do we have here? I think I see a fellow lover of adventure, and I'm betting it's no accident that you're headed this way.nnAm I right? Have Rivenspire's troubles become your troubles too?

Ha! The Baandari scouts said they could see the flames from here! Let's celebrate!nnActually, I hope you don't mind, but I went ahead and started celebrating. After everything that's happened here, I deserved a drink. Silver-Paws did, too.
Don't worry about me. We should keep moving. Can't stop moving.
Oh, look at you! This one tells me you're some big winner. That is  impressive. I am impressed.nnPlease, retire. I should hope to have some chance of your title.
It is done. No one shall ever suffer at the hands of this accursed creation again.
You have shown me more kindess than I deserve. I shall spend my remaining days attempting to atone and truly honor my son's memory.
The soldiers must stay here. They must hold this position or all will be lost.

My fellow Baandari said they saw the Imperial boats burning down by the water. You have certainly turned things around here.nnThe Knight Commander was quite eager to start celebrating. I don't mind humoring her.
Thanks for your intervention at North Glen. nnOnce these soldiers recover, we'll mop up any filthy Reachmen that remain.
Stonefalls is lucky to have our strong arms and sharp blades. It must look like home to Molag Bal. At least, that's my explanation for all the anchors.
I've heard some crazy stories, but the way those bandits robbed the townposing as the constable and his deputythat's just pure madness.
I have to say, I'm not too keen on having a mayor that was so quick to compromise with bandits. nnI know they were holding his wife, but  well, that's another reason I'm not getting married.
So the constable's got her old job back? Am I supposed to offer her a toast? I don't think so.
When a woman opens up to you and really lets herself be vulnerable, that's your chance. You just have to take it.
Gods! What happened to Miss Mondorie is so unfair. It could have been any of us too!
Gods! This bread  it's amazing! I mean, I've never had such good bread!nnI think it's the town miller. Ghak really knows his trade.
I've been waiting for my husband to return from Northpoint for weeks. If something happened to him, I just don't know what I would do with myself.
I think the constable should run for mayor. She's a much better leader than that coward of a bureaucrat who currently holds the office.
I'm glad we're all friends again, but my brother's still missing. I have half a mind to march up to Northpoint myself and try to find him.
I thought the mayor had fired Agazu because she was an Orc. Sad as all this was, I'm glad to learn that's not the case.
I'm so glad someone will finally listen to me. My husband never wanted to do anything more than share my bed.
I think the whole lot of those militia ruffians should be strung up from the highest tree!
What happened to Lady Mondorie is unforgiveable!nnSomeone has to do something about Rivenspire's bandit problem. They just have to!
After all this heartache, we're just supposed to forgive and forget? Not likely!
I'm glad Constable Agazu got her job back. She almost drank all my reserves in one night!
I heard the mayor stepped down from office. Who's going to keep the streets clean now?

Thank the moons! As I was just explaining, that thief nearly ran us over. You chased after him.nnPlease, tell this fine keeper of the peace what you saw. I'm still sore from the last night I spent in the stocks!
Not to worry, citizen. This fleabitten scoundrel will not trouble you. Jode's Chariot will see to that.
Now that Shornhelm is secure, we can turn our attention to the reports coming in from the rest of Rivenspire. Something definitely unusual is going on out there.
The Eight Divines are running a little behind.nnWe mustn't mention it when they arrive. It's important to remain polite when in the presence of divinity.
The Light has shown us the way. It has restored Shornhelm and it will see us through to the ultimate defeat of Baron Montclair.
They came into my house. Tried to take my fire from me.nnSo I showed them. The fire is a part of me, now. It will always be inside me!

The priest fears the unknown. That is why he refuses to acknowledge the gift the prince has been given.nnBut why do you submit to this priest's direction? Are you a coward, or do you just prefer not to think for yourself?

The town's safe, I guess. It's a wreck, and nobody who was crazy really seems to be getting better.nnI guess I need to think about my future from this point. But, let's look on the bright side. Look at how many things I have to sell!
Oh, I suppose I heard the mayor did all this. I suppose he must've gone a little mad.nnWe all go a little mad, now and then. Perfectly normal. Do you know when he will be back?
It's at times like these when my commitment as a priest are truly tested. I will support my community and continue prayers until Southpoint is restored to its previous glory.
The constable says my job is just to sit here and look pretty.nnI think I'm doing that fairly well.
If you could find a way to get all those corpses back in the ground while you're up there, I sure would appreciate that.nnI can't make a living if I can't get into the graveyard!
Pardon my saying so, but you are obviously doing well for yourself. What brought you here?
Finally, the town has started to settle down. Maybe I can hear myself think now.
Deepswimmer just went for one more dive! He came back to find this troll eating all his friends!nnPraise the moons you came along! Did you come from the Martyr's Crossing?
Paws of Rajhin tread with you, my friend.
Don't feel bad for me. I got what was coming to me.nnI trusted Peras.
That was a timely rescue. If you hadn't come by, slavers would have hauled us halfway across Tamriel by next week.nnProbably would've learned a lot from the tripwould've seen a lot, too. As slaves.
Thank you for freeing us. I didn't think bandits would ever want anything with a couple of scholars on a boat.nnWhy would you ever board a ship with Peras on it? Come to think of it, why did I?

While you go to Camp Tamrith and help deal with Reezal-Jul, I shall look into the gaps in my memory that you helped uncover. There must be something important in the hills to the east. Why else would the mad Argonian have taken those memories?
I knew my neighbors were innocent! Now maybe things around here can get back to normal.

Of course! You can go to Hallin's Stand! Fabulous idea!nnYes, my friend. The key to driving the Imperials out of southern Bangkorai will be finding and  eliminating the Magus General. If you'll track Septima down, we'll be halfway done.
Whatever's in the crypt, it must be destroyed. Whether it be Imperial, undead, Daedra  just kill it. Kill it all.
It is as they saythe Hollow Moon provides, yes?
You look like someone who appreciates strong leadership. That's in short supply around here, but I'm sure you already noticed that.
A good day at the market! Sula will be so happy!
There's usually not much happening in the village, but today's an exception, isn't it?nnYou don't need to buy anything, do you?
I thought I recognized you! You were right in the middle of those Imperial bastards. nnAnd, hey  didn't you also kill that hag back in Jackdaw Cove? By Stendarr's shield, I'm talking to a legend!
What's taking so long? I can only wait around for so long!
Maybe next time, those maul-brained rock-herders will bring me some food! Squirrels can only last you so long, you know?
Do you smell that? The air here, it's almost sweet.nnBe wary. There are vampires about and that smell means they're on the prowl. It's best you didn't wander alone.
Can't, I can't  I .
Self sacrifice is rare these days. I hope Captain Gaercroft is finally proud of his daughter. Not that he wasn't. Perhaps now he'll finally show just how much she meant to him.
His shaking has slowed. Perhaps, when he wakes, he will be cured of his addiction.
Tell me, have you seen my nose? I think it must have fallen off somewhere. I can't smell a thing.
Have you found Puddles yet? She enjoys chasing sheep, so you might look for her near livestock.
You'll find <<1>> standing vigil over his sons in one of the caves.
And what do you want? Come to stare at the fallen warrior?
By the Eight! Can you feel the relic's power, Verandis?
Such foul creatures! I hope no one gets hurt because of me.
And yet again, we will teach someone to guard that which guards its own.
With the Mad Architect gone, I'll admit  this place has a homely look.nnI've work to do. If I could learn what he learnedperhaps I could fill his role.
Have to say, a little violence and mayhem always clears my head. It's exhilirating!
Do you smell that? The air here, it's almost sweet.nnBe wary. There are vampires about and that smell means they're on the prowl. It's best you didn't wander alone.
We shall see to it that the Viridian Sentinel learns what it means to be a guardian of the woods.
Can I finish my prayer please? I think you have things to do.
You are the one who liberated Hallin's Stand, is it not so? Your deeds are known to us here. Ruptga's blessings be upon you.
Thank you, my friend. For all you've done.nnBut it seems our hardship isn't over yet.
Thank you for helping us. There's  not much else you can do.nnI hope Gasteau has a plan. Staying here seems  unwise.
We raise hardy horses here in the Rift, and hardier people. Can I interest you in one of our fine animals?
You'll find no better steed in all the Rift! My Pa breeds nothing but the best.
Condemn these pitiful souls to their fate.
Greetings, walker. This one sees that you have a five-clawed look. You wish to join the Guild, yes?
This place is abysmal. Hardly anything to read. Buzzards squawking day and night. Say  what's that you're carrying?
Hold a moment. What business have you in Bangkorai Garroh. A thousand pardons, I didn't recognize you. Welcome back, sir.
You've been a great help, friend.
This one thinks the knights are lucky the Baandari were here!
I can't thank you enough for ridding Pelin Graveyard of the Prince's treachery. nnIt's bad enough that our knights get killed by Imperial dogs. Having them raised as undead is more than I could bear.
I've hired other adventurers to gather more information for my second book, the Bigger Book of Bloodfiends, but I need you for a special task.
Sleek fighting, walker. You and Crazy Eye make a good team.
Thank you for your help. You've saved many lives.
Watch where you step. Bandit corpses get a little mushy.

The war is far from over, but we've won a crucial battle. Definitely gave the Imperials a black eye. nnAnd Evermore is safe. I should return there, but I have a feeling Emeric will want to press on to liberate Southern Bangkorai.
Is that really my great-grandmother's sword? She was a mighty warrior, or so the stories say.
You have it, yes? The treasure?
We raise fine horses in Davon's Watch. Once sold one to Vivec himself. What can I help you with?
Stay your hand and hear my words. Dominion, Pact, Covenantyou're like schoolchildren fighting over marbles, while the world around you is on fire.
Ah, a hatchling in search of wisdom. Are you acquainted with the Mages Guild, my friend? You would do well to join us. What is it that you carry?
Meet Adusa at Montclair Manor, Five-Claws. It's in Shornhelm's upper city. This one must clean up here first, or Verandis will become very cross. He hates it when we play with our food.
<Cariel's bottle no longer holds a message. It now sits empty, a nonsequiteur for the next passerby.>
I trust we can rely on you to be discreet about your involvement with us.

Sometimes I wonder if such a narrow field of study has stunted my growth as a mage. Perhaps there's more to life than just portals.nnThen I think of how instrumental they were in ending the Blacksap Rebellion. Makes it all worthwhile.

Adusa is so happy she could just purr! The fighting, the blood, the excitementAdusa hasn't had so much fun in an Elf's age!nnAnd, yes, we ended another threat to Rivenspire. That, too. All in all, Adusa had a fine, fine day.
I'm glad you came to your senses about <<1>>. He asked me to verify any ore we find, so here I am.nnLet's get this over with.
What have you found out?
What have you found out?
What have you found out?

You! You were the one who slipped that draught into my mug, were you not? I cannot believe I fell for that. nnThis isn't right, you know. It was the oppressiveness of Redguard society that drove me to become a bandit. Yes. I blame society.
Leave me alone. I'm only here for the wine.
She's warming up to me. I can tell.
You know, now that he's gone, I almost miss the way that bailiff stared at my bottom. No one else around here seems to even notice me anymore.
I'm just trying to have a quiet drink.
I'm just trying to have a quiet drink.

Yes. I would say our experiment was quite a success. I bet you want another one of those trinkets, don't you?nnWell, don't fret. I'm going to craft crates of the things! Look for me on the road. I might even give you one on the house.
Can't you just leave a man to his drinks?
Can't you just leave a man to his drinks?
I'm working up the nerve to go back over to my usual chair at the table. I just keep thinking I hear that bailiff coming back.
What can I do for you?
What can I do for you?
It may take time, but these traitors will have their day in the sun.
Find that man of mine, will you? Next time he wanders off with the pup, he's going to have to get Xandier to drag him back.
You know, when I was attacked by those wolves, the thought crossed my mind that I might never see my Nathalye again. I  I don't know how to thank you.
<<<1>> bounces back and forth and does a little spin. He looks like he wants you to follow.>
So you're really going up there? Well, better you than me.nnI'll be right here when you're ready to return to Northpoint.
The Eight guide you. The jouney there may not be easy.
Montclair started this war, but I plan to finish it. My soldiers will be ready to move at a moment's notice.
I regret I could not give you more, but I have little. Service to Arkay is its own reward.
I can't believe the Knight Commander's willing to give those bows to those backstabbing Baandari. I'm going to report this to  well, to someone.
I'm very sorry. I wish we could do more for the Garrison.
So the brave Baron Dorell is your choice then. I know he's valiant warrior and I expect he will make a wise and honorable king. nnKing Alard of Shornhelm. It even has a nice ring to it.
As long as there are rotting corpses, I'll have a job.
My aid, Clerk Cantier, should be somewhere near Traitor's Tor. With any luck, he has a solid lead as to the location of the missing Crown of Shornhelm.
Tell the vampire that we need his tricks no longer. The Light will guide us to the destruction of the remnant.
My family is indebted to you.nnI remember your goodwill after our trial declares me the rightful king of Valenwood.

We've come through much to reach this point. We won a battle for the very soul of Rivenspire.nnNow comes the responsibility of rebuilding the kingdom. I hope High King Emeric gives me the opportunity to lead us through the difficulties ahead.

It's a miracle that we survived and triumphed over Montclair. Thanks, in no small part, to my steady leadership.nnMay Arkay grant the High King the wisdom to see that I am the best choice to lead Rivenspire.
You have proven most useful, unlike many before you.
Look at that spire. Rather menacing, don't you think? I should be nervous, but the thought of climbing up there  it's pretty exciting!
Interesting item, this Orb of Discourse. I must find a way to use it to determine the location of Sai Sahan.
If anybody can find out where they're holding Sai, the Prophet can. We'll find him.
I'll see you on the other side, my friend. Stay safe out there.
<<1>> is honored! Tell me, what have you brought? Spices? Gemstones, perhaps?
The worst part of ending the Blacksap threat? Now is when I need to be most vigilant. Convincing yourself the snake has no fangs is usually when it learns to constrict.

You were the one who tried to talk me into moving to Shornhelm and doing some honest work, weren't you?nnI am so glad I didn't do that. We're making more coin than I ever dreamed possible now. And to think, I almost quit right before the miracle.

I'm expecting you to come back here with at least a few Reachmen heads hanging from your belt. nnWe can mount them on the city walls. I wonder what Captain Hjurrun did with old Strastnoc's head  we should get that one up there too.
We need to give you a nickname. Something like "The Knife."nnHmm. How about "The Doomsmasher?" That sounds a little dark, I guess. I'll think about it.

After a long talk with the Countess, it was decided that it would be best if I looked for other employment.nnI think she was just having a hard time dealing with her feelings for me. I expect she'll get all weepy when I'm gone.
<<<1>> bounces back and forth under your hand. He looks like he wants you to follow.>
How could you pick her? Under her the army will grow lazy and fat.
The longer I'm here, the better that mead looks. I think I might head back to Fell's Run soon.
Please, look for my family. I miss my dear <<1>>!nnAnd <<2>>, of course.
I knew <<1>> wouldn't leave me. We've spent a lot of time in  my wife's homeland of <<2>>, so the unusual fauna here must have spooked him a bit.
So my lady convinced you to help her? Of course she did. She's ever so good at that.nnWell, be careful in there. I'll save you some stew for when you get back.
So, you are the ring's next victim.
It is done
target: the ring is gone. No one will ever suffer this madness again.

source: You have shown me more kindess than I deserve. I will spend my remaining days atoning for the wrongs I have done.
It is done. No one shall ever suffer at the hands of this accursed creation again.
Take good care of the Champions, Hallowed. We are all counting on you. Until Dune, then.
The Champions are in your hands, Hallowed. Keep them safe, and be careful. The path to the Mane is fraught with danger, heartbreak, and sacrifice.
Though I am the last of Alvaren's knights, I remain steadfast in his cause.
I was just about to go in after you. Thought maybe you were stuck in a cage or something.
A new recruit, eh? I hope you can keep pace. The blood will run fast and thick when the vampires attack, and I can't watch your back and mine.
Are you ready to take the sword to these abberrations, Oblivion's own children?
Karnosis bound my spirit to this place when he failed to save me. I've watched what he's become  what he's turned into. He is not the man I once loved, though his intentions never changed.
Thanks for helping Garth. I'd offer you something to drink, but we drank it all.
Oh, Divines, it was terrible. The spider queen was huge. She had sixteen legs! Or was I seeing double?nnThank you for saving me.
<<1>> is of such importance to <<2>>. I've heard the stories since I was a child, and always wondered what would happen should it be restored.nnI suppose I'll learn very soon.
<<1>> has finally arrived. Just in time for the ratification ceremony to begin.nnI'm sure she will commend you for your efforts.
I suppose a wanderer like you wouldn't know what "busy" looks like.nnI will demonstrate. Feel free to observe. Quietly, and from a distance.
Ohh  Mara bless me. Are you real?
So much death, so many lost dreams. They never told me the world was full of so much grief.nnBut there I go again. Gurlarz would be ashamed to hear me carrying on like this.
I already told you. Access to the storeroom is restricted. If you want to get in, show me written orders from the ambassador.
Thank you for returning Firaelion to me. He may be a fool, but he is a sweet one.
Thanks, friend. I was this close to becoming those spiders' next meal. At least I managed to gather some silk for Mendil. She'll have her dress yet. She deserves it.
We have work to do, but with the threat of a briar heart removed, the rest will be easier.
Thanks for all you've done.

I'm not sure how much time I have, but thank you for what you've done. My sacrifice is nothing compared to your brave response to Hircine's challenge.nnCan I help you understand this realm, a place of shadow, hunger, and thirst?
My hunter returns, briar heart in hand. Brinarch now roams my Hunting Grounds as prey. His chest, a gaping hollow, a reminder of his weakness. Heed his punishment, pup.
I owe you my sincere gratitude. Why, if Stibbons were stuck as a statue forever, I don't know what I'd do!nnIt simply doesn't bear thinking about.
Elriniel was just bringing me up to speed. It sounds like you've been busy, my friend. You've impressed the Elf, and that isn't an easy thing to do. Well done!
Did you just say what I think you said? The assassin is dead?nnThank the Eight! Now maybe I can get back to my normal schedule.

I have to admit, fighting alongside you was kind of fun!nnWith Maugruhl dead, the Bitterhand bandits are just another sorry lot of bandits scraping by. Not too bright, disorganized and easier to deal with.
They call this place <<c:1>> because it's where all the refuse ends up. We clear them out now and again, but they always come back.nnNecessary evil, I'm told.
I heard something about the Wyrd In my opinion, it's good news.nnThey're far better-equipped to understand what we are fighting than we are, ourselves.
Are you ready? And can you stop thinking so loudly?
If Reezal-Jul escaped, we will have to track him down. He and Montclair both.nnI fear Montclair's ambitions may be far greater than simply conquering all of Rivenspire. It's better we stop him now.
Do you have any wine? If I'm to spend the rest of my days in this hole, I think I'll develop a drinking problem.
Neither of us will forget your kindness.

Did I hear that right? You went looking for my necklace? You found it, and brought it back? The Eight preserve us, thank you!nnAnd if that loveable galoot doesn't ask me to marry him, I will! You just wait!
Adusa needs some time to think about this. There are other problems that must be dealt with.nnTalk to Darien.
Find the tear in the veil and let's eliminate another shard holder.
Good job. I'm not sure why you got yourself involved in all this, but I don't care. You did well.

<<1>> shouldn't be hard to track. You can smell him leagues away. But if I leave town, the treethane will send people after me, thinking I'm trying to escape with his bow.nnI can't do a thing until I get that bow back.
No. Not <<1>>. I'm such a fool. Clearly the vampire lord saw through our trap. <<1>>'s death is on my head.
Well, my family is at peace now. Thank you so much for your help. You'll always be a friend of the Hinault family.
I just miss them so much. What will I do without them?

Warmth like the sun's. We are free of the Elf-things' prison. We apologize for what we tried to do. nnWe were mad with hunger, unable to nourish ourselves within the wallswe were not ourselves. The air feeds us, now.

I heard what happened in Sentinel  it was worse than I feared, but I have faith. nnThe people of the Alik'r desert are resilient and unyielding like the sands of the great cliffs and the shores of the Ancestors themselves.
In my mind's eye, I witnessed your battle with the Worm Cult, and with the undead Ansei abominations. Your mission was successful, was it not?
You call this justice? The Vinedusk used you, just as the Dominion used them. You've done nothing but tighten the grasp of tyranny on <<1>>.
Prisoner Line 1
Prisoner Line 1
Prisoner Line 1
Prisoner Line 1

Things have quieted down for the moment. But I will need more than a day of peace between the races to secure my position.nnKing Camoran has suggested we use the Orrery to settle matters. I have my doubts, but am rather strapped for an alternative.
This is  ook  terrible! How ever am I going to serve my lady now?nnOh, bother! I guess I'd better start packing up the camp.
With all that gold, I'll be able to buy enough balm to cure me. I'll be well again! And have plenty left over for food, and rent, and  oh, Nedras.

I couldn't ask you to risk your life, but you look like you can handle yourself, and truthfully, I wouldn't mind if the Worm Cultists found themselves in a little trouble. nnTake this crystal and use it to gather the light from the Ayleid Well.
Oh that mead is going to taste so good. Mead today, a blade tomorrow. That's my plan! Forget that stupid mule!
Yenadar's grace be upon you traveler. And Kala's prayers go with you as well.
The king will know what to do. He listens to his people! The Dominion would be in a better place if he were in charge.
To go back on one's word is a serious thing. If <<1>> cannot construct an embassy, how can she build the Dominion?
You have cleared away the weeds so that I may set down new roots and thrive.nnSomeday, I hope I can do the same for another and repeat the cycle.
Bright moons shine on you, friend. This one's belly is full, thanks to you! nnNow we must haggle with knights over whose goods are whose. Commerce! Mazurr cannot wait!
You should talk to the Baron. I'm ready to go hit something, but he's been waiting to talk to you before he gives us any new orders.
You picked the right place at the right time, comrade. With so many knights injured here, there's great demand for fighters willing to take their places.
Good work rock-stomping that Imperial trash. Mauloch knows those knights couldn't do it alone.
I was at the garrison when it fell. My vision went red, I went berserk and  well, I don't remember much after that.
Heard the gravedigger has to bury that poor Orc who went missing up near the <<1>>. Such a shame.
I see the Garrison's been retaken. The Guild doesn't take sides in conflicts like this. nnAs Ufgabesh the student mage, I say nothing. But as Ufgabesh the Orc, I say "Well done."
When times are darkest, knowledge is what's needed to bring back the light. nnWhat's that you have there? A book?
I hear the Garrison has been retaken. Thank you, my friend. I do not think I will see its walls again, but  but I know they are in good hands.
The hill. Climb the hill.
We couldn't have retaken the Garrison without you. nnAlas, I haven't time for celebration. More wounded arrive by the hour. May the Eight help us.
With each new wolf, our pack becomes stronger. You're one of us now.
Darien's probably got himself caught and gutted in the officer's house.nnNo way we can get in there though without a key. They keep it locked tight.
By Zenithar, I have an acute throbbing in my cranium. Could this be what a hangover is like?
Blessings of St. Pelin be upon you, friend. We couldn't have retaken the fort without you.
I thought the Garrison was lost for good. I've never been so glad to be proven wrong.

Truthfully, I think a few days rest are well-deserved on both our partsnot at the seashore, mind you, but perhaps in Wayrest.nnUnfortunately though, I am long overdue for an appoinment. And as it happens, so are you.
I suppose the Baandari helped a bit. But I hardly think launching a few arrows at retreating Imperials evens the score.

You are a brave soul to go after the king on your own. I applaud your courage. nnI will go to Evermore to request additional support. Then I will return. May Ruptga and all the gods be with you until then.
If the Covenant does have a portal down there, it's vital that we close it.nnDon't worry about fighting everyone in there. Just focus on finding the portal. Then let the wand do the rest.
This wasn't supposed to happen here. Today should have been a celebration, but instead .nnInstead, none of this officially happened.
Thanks again for killing that blood-stained bandit, Sgolag. Stay vigilant, our enemies will not rest, and we must persevere.
I had my doubts about <<1>>. Not after today.nnTravel well, my friend.
Thank you. It will mean a lot to me to have my notes back, at least. Be careful. Aggravated kwama are dangerous, to say nothing of the thunderbugs.
Remember, "the vines are strongest at dusk." The king will know you're a friend.
A final challenge for us both. This should be easy.
Do you accept my power?
Adeena's family may forgive me, but I will never forgive myself.
We need to find Najan.
It is good to be free of him. With my sister gone, there's nothing keeping me here. nnI have never seen the sea. Perhaps my days in Bangkorai are over.
What can Sabani get this child of Alkosh?

Whatever you do, keep an eye out for any members of my gang. I can't believe they gave up without a fight, but I can believe they're all holed up somewhere. Probably hiding out until this all blows over.
Our kind live in darkness and feed on life. Walking among us requires forsaking the gods and embracing the blessing of Mother Lamae. Will you proceed?
Sometimes I wonder if Ufa is still here at all. They say he's in hiding, but why?
We don't see a lot of travelers these days. What brought you here?

Were it truly your time, I might invite you to remain here in the Far Shores. You have earned the right to be here.nnIt is not your time though, so you must go. Take your liege back, restore him, and then you must all leave the Hall of Heroes.
The sooner this is over the better.
Ah, to see out of Khajiit eyes again! Zur hates being caged in that dark place.
The couple despairs, but all is not lost! Nothing is without hope, until the last breath!nnLet me tell you of their child. Come, come!
Everyone owes you so much. We'll never be able to repay you. I, especially, shall pray to the gods for your continued health and good fortune.
You got what you came for! Now leave me be!
Welcome to Trader's Meet, my friend. Come for a selection of rarities, have you?nnWell, how about  apples! Guaranteed to be worm-free! They're imported from Glenumbra.
Remember. Move slowly and enter the tunnel one at a time. If we raise any alarms, this mission will be over before it's begun.nnGo on. We'll follow right behind you.
Everything you see comes from something I killed myself. In <<1>>, we use what we hunt.
Honor my mother's sacrifice and you will earn my blessing.
I suppose you don't have any jagga, do you? So delicious  if I could, I'd drink it straight from the pig!
My husband spends so much time with his books. I can never pull him away, especially when it's time to hunt.
Talk to my father if you're looking for potions. We don't keep our stock here.
Damned treethane, thinks she knows what's best for <<1>>. Wasn't born here, wasn't raised here. If I didn't know any better, I'd say she's a plant from <<2>>.
I don't know how my neighbors can walk the streets. Everywhere I go, I see where the Jade Butcher's troops killed my friends.
Look for the Packmaster. Just follow the scent. The pounding in your blood will tell you when you're close. You'll find him. I know it. He'll teach you the secrets of Hircine's gift.
What do you want from me? I have nothing more. Nothing! No home, no family. No future .
You must think as a sword-singer would. Which blade would be most suitable for a warrior who has achieved mastery of his or her technique?

It appears the curse has been lifted. Whatever you did, it must have worked. Now I have all the time I need to study the ruins and piece the whole story together.nnDon't worry. I'll mention your name in my book!
When the Imperials invaded, I was deep in my cup. They took my sword before it even left the sheath.
I wondered if someone would find me, before they finished me off.
You don't look like one of the Seventh Legion. Why have you come?
Drink deep from my gift.

Remember, if you find Lleraya, don't talk to her. Don't try to reason with her. Just kill her before she can seduce you with her vampiric wiles.nnAnd if you find any survivors, send them back here where we can protect them.
Go on, I'll meet you outside. Need to make sure things are nice and tidy in here.
The Briars can always use more skilled hunters. If you think you can prove your mettle, speak with <<1>> in <<2>>.
The wood weeps. Can you hear it too? Is that why you've come?
It is an honor to serve Queen Maraya.
Isn't she beautiful? And so enchanting! Please, sit beside me and we can gaze upon dear Lady Lleraya together.
You should hurry to the Earth Forge, comrade, but if you have urgent questions, please ask me.
Please enjoy our attractions. I'm terribly sorry they're so limited at the moment.
The corruption is gone. All of it.
I know you  your spirit, but you belong in this place no more than the others, the invaders.nnWhy do you come here? Why do you disturb my rest?

Don't worry about me. I'll throw on some armor and go with Gwendis. Put the old team back together!nnBut first I need to leave a flower for the lovely captain here. Give her something to remember me by.
Bah. Silver-Paws is a fool to share sugar with those knights. They pretend they are our friends now. If we are attacked by more Imperials though, we will see their true spots.
You check out the wrecked boats and I'll gather the others.nnHopefully, by the time we meet you at the tunnel, you'll have a lead on getting us that key.
Well, the Imperials did not fall for my clever rusebut Naradani thinks this is not a total loss. This one can think of many uses for Khajiiti decoys. Some of them are even legal!
Welcome to <<1>>. How can I assist you with your import and export needs?
I'm not performing at the moment. I'm sure <<1>> could inform you of the carnival's schedule.
These poultices are Divine-sent. I fear I may have cursed those poor merchants in the throes of my fever. nnIf you  if you see them, thank them for me.
Good luck finding <<Amz:1>>!nnOnly if you have the time. I realize it's not the most glamorous request.
Care to spend some of that gold you've earned, dearie?nnAnd before you ask, I'm all out of boar knuckles. You wouldn't believe the demand on those things.
What are you doing here? You found your spy. The soldiers came for Edouard, all right. I can imagine what they're doing to him. He'll hang, thanks to you.
I'm sorry, but I have nothing to say.
I'll stay here and keep guard over the survivors in my care. But I will also remain vigilant, ready to lend my blade as soon as Baron Alard needs it.
You're all a bunch of tyrants!
Good show! The Wood Elves need to learn their place. Speaking out against Queen Ayrenn is treason!nnEspecially when she saved their ungrateful lives.
Without you, we all would be dead now. I pray for our friends who did not survive, and I will also offer prayers of thanks for you.
Take the boat over when your ready.nnYou could always head back into Northpoint and see how the town's doing too.
Follow your blood. It will lead you to Rahaja.nnPerhaps we will be kin one day.
Yes, how can I help you?
It seems that the only thing more loathesome than <<1>> writing his own opinions for posterity  may be the opinions that he ends up recycling from the scholars who have died here.
Hm. Not my usual type, but business is slow. What can I do for you?
Who are you? What have you done with Niha? What was in that wine?
You're amazing. Just amazing! I hope to be half the warrior as you some day. Thank you for everything.

Now all I have to do is locate that wildlife specimen Azei calls our pet. If only I'd had that monkey <<1>> stuffed when we first found him, we'd know precisely where he is!nnAh, well. We could always go back to the <<2>> for another if need be.

You actually survived the destruction of the Doomcrag? That's  remarkable.nnI mean, I've seen you do some amazing things. I'll never forget our adventures in Glenumbra. But to walk out of a collapsed mountain? That's really impressive.
You an archer? Nah, I bet you like that personal touch. Axes, right?  nnEither way, I've got a weapon for you!
You've brought my business back to life, wayfarer! Soon this sleepy market will be a bustling bazaar again!
My, my, mywhat have you done to your clothes? Slaying Imperials is hard on the garments, yes? You should treat yourself to a new wardrobe. Look aroundyou earned it.
My, my, mywhat have you done to your clothes? Slaying Imperials is hard on the cloth, yes? You should treat yourself to a new wardrobe. Look aroundyou earned it.
I suppose saving a city is worth a drink.
Big day today! I bagged three scamps and a very grumpy atronach. You keeping up?
You know, I was in the Imperial army once. Seeing what you did to those Legionaries  makes me glad I deserted.
Hail, comrade. I trust the Daedra culling is proceeding at pace? nnRumor has it the God of Schemes has been working double shifts to keep up with you.
I guess a drink or two wouldn't hurt.
Ruptga bless you for ridding the city of those twice-cursed Imperials. I had planned to poison their drinking water, but I suppose your way  sent a message?

Hm. Perhaps your interest is genuine. I will gladly accept your help. From the size and shape, I would say we need four more pieces. The fisherman claimed he was fishing off the western coast when this stone was found. The others might not be far.
Go on now. Find your friend. Let me do my job.

Don't suppose you killed an Imperial carrying a cask of pomegranate wine? Sand snake made off with one before the fighting started. nnAh, well. It is a small price to pay for clean streets. Can I get you something?
That's all I know. I swear it. Now move on, would you?
By Mauloch's left fang! Those whoreson dogs! Sons of trolls! The First Forge burn them!nnOgre dung!
Get her out of here. I'll cover your retreat.
Shut the door quickly behind you. The sand gets into everything, especially the alchemical equipment.nnWhat have you got there? A book?
Nicolene and I will be headed back to Sentinel soon enough. Until then, you should stay and have a drink with us.
Glad to get some fresh air. I can only take the smell of incense for so long, and the Imperials had us locked up for days.
My fellow mages are good folk, but I must confess I'm glad the lock-down is over. If I had to listen to one more debate about the merits of alteration over conjuration, I would have lost my mind.
<Esmaeel lies motionless.>
Khajiit is happy to meet someone who understands us. Malira thought the Elves would be more welcoming.
Why do you encourage her behavior? These blasted cat people need to learn that some customs will not be accepted in the Dominion!nnI'm glad it's not people like you making the rules around here.
Ah, the Empire's bane graces us with a visit! Welcome to The Drowsy Owl, friend. I have readied my most lavish suite for you. Only the best for the hero of Hallin's Stand!

You are the hero everyone speaks about, is it not so? There was an Imperial shouting your name as he fled out the back window, and by Tava's red feathers, there was terror in his voice. nnWe can but hope he survived. Someone must tell the tale.
Please. No more. I can't take any more .
As weary as we are, we can't wait to be on the road. I was so eager to see the world when I joined the legion. Now I just want to see home again.
foo
<No new scouting missions are available.>
Next time I get handed a contract with the words mage, magus, wizard, spell or anything even remotely magic-related, I'm just going to quit.
<A few of this dusty journal's pages have their corners folded inward to mark specific entries.>
So where's <<1>>? Did the Daedra get her, or did she escape?

Tall Papa's blessings be upon you, my friend. The Imperials had been lusting for our library for some time. I fear that had you not intervened, they would have taken our books by force. There are those in Cyrodiil quite desperate for such knowledge.

I received word the Imperials have been routed. I pray it is true. nnLong and long have been the days since they arrived. Their spell-weavers have been watching us with envious eyes. If we had lost our library to those barbarians.
New good-looking friend has returned! With the <<1>>?
Hmph. It has its own archaic charm, I'll admit.
I don't intend to tell anyone what my brother did. As far as I'm concerned, he died trying to help me, not usurp my throne.
What happened to <<1>> was a tragedy.nnI hope that sounds believeable. I'll be saying it for the rest of my days.
<No new warfront missions are available.>
<The Bounty board has a spot for me to post my report.>
<No new battle missions are available.>
What a relief. I fared better than most during the occupation. nnBut the things that my patrons saw! By Tava's red feathers, I shudder to think of it.
<No new scouting missions are available.>
<No new warfront missions are available.>
<The Bounty board has a spot for me to post my report.>
<No new battle missions are available.>
<No new scouting missions are available.>
<No new warfront missions are available.>
<The Bounty board has a spot for me to post my report.>
<No new battle missions are available.>
Ah, hello. I always have time for Guild members.nnHow may I be of assistance?
Well you made quite a mess out there. Damn glad I don't have to clean it up.
Don't try to reason with <<1>>. Just go with what she says. She's crazy as an Alfiq-raht in heat.nnIf you have any other questions, ask <<2>>. She's up front with our cart.
If you need my assistance, I shall need to know the nature of your emergency.nnOtherwise, it would be prudent of you to reconsider my time, which you are wasting.

By Tall Papa's starry breeches, it is good to be rid of those stinking Imperial curs. I would offer you a drink on the house had they not plundered my cellar. A simple "thanks" will have to suffice.nnIt is just a pity that you did not come sooner.
Ha ha ha! Gave him a good scare didn't I? Maybe that'll make him think twice before tearing a flower from the ground.nnThat felt good. Some people just have no class.
Thank you for soothing that Wood Elf's temper.nnHe would've taken a hand, an arm, or worse, if you hadn't come along.
I should never have sent you to do my own work. I am a strong Orc, and proud. I do not need the help of an outsider.
Don't worry. We won't linger here any longer than we have to.
Oh, yes, come closer . Hmm  how strong you look with my minion's blood on your hands .
Please tell my dear sister that I'm still waiting for that apology.
My beloved brother has a better chance of squeezing fire salts from an ice cube than getting an apology from me.
You can have the relic if you want it. Needless to say, I won't be taking it with me. That should get me a discount from Dragonstar Caravans, shouldn't it?
Probably only a matter of time before the Imperials anger everyone. I told my friend he could come with me, but he's too attached to this city.nnI suppose I understand that.
Back already, eh? I'm sure my charges are happy to know you tried, even if you couldn't get their things back.nnWe'll be able to head out now!
His honor is intact.
Don't dally now. If you take too long, I might just have to retake the garrison without you.
A pleasure to have you with us, friend. I look forward to recovering the valuables from your corpse!
Thanks, mate. Now to find an Imperial's throat to bury this dagger into .
Thank you. I'm happy to have something to remember my wife by. Now when the winds blow, I will imagine her singing again.
Thank you so much. I hope to wear this on my wedding day.
I am eternally grateful for this act of kindness. With this, my daughter's future is safe.
<<1>> could not wait for you to return. My sister gave him an end befitting a warrior.nnKeep the helmet of his foewe do not need reminders of this folly.
Let me know when you kill a real monster. Or if you'd like to try this monster on for size .
Thanks for the drink, sweetheart.nnMaybe when you bring back the head of a lich I'll buy you one. Probably not.

This one has heard much less unrest. Kitten-headed fools trusting the High Elves to deliver on their promises.nnAzimsun will believe this when he sees the truth of it for himself. Too much has been witnessed to be blindly hopeful, yes?

This one hears the most wonderful news, yes? The embassy for all walkers is to be constructed as planned.nnVabashi knew all she needed to do was hold fast. There was no break of promise, merely  delays.

This one serves the Dominion well, and knows many others are the same way as he. What happens when all we disgruntled walkers refuse to fight for Elves who do nothing for us? Battles will be lostthis I promise.
Nerien'eth took everything from me.nnAnd I won't rest until I take something back.
