It's easier to form coherent thoughts when I'm not being stabbed. It's been a long couple of years.nnI owe you a debt, friend. I'll never forget what you did for us. For Alanwe.
The others have been singing your praises, but with a little more time, I would have gathered the magicka to free myself.nnIn another decade or so. It's hard to concentrate when you're on fire.
Good luck sneaking in through the muck. If you don't manage it, we're all dead.
Please! Don't let them kill me!

I prayed to Arkay for guidance in death  I didn't realize he would send the voices of the dead to speak to me alone.nnHow can I possibly do the bidding of the wronged deceased? I care for the bodies of the dead, I do not fight!
I miss Buttons. nnWithout him, everything is grey, and each day is worse than the one before.
Go ahead. I do not like being watched while I climb. It is awkward.
Ha! You are so pathetic  it just makes me laugh. I think we should be friends.nnMaybe later, I'll tell you about Buttons and our circle of love.
<He appears to have been dead for some time.>
Clanmother must be obeyed promptly! Snap to it, you hear? Remember what I said, when you're sad that you didn't listen to me.
Excuse me. Might you be willing to do us a favor and run a message to Evermore Castle?
Thank you for the coin, I'm eternally thankful.
I'll see if I can get closer to the Imperial dogs to surmise their true purpose. Wish me luck, friend.
Thank you for bringing this information to me. I will send word to Evermore right away.
I think before I said I had seen it all . Well, I was wrong.
Praise Tu'whacca! Is it  is it really him?
I can't believe it! I carried that lockbox around for years!
I'll see you out at those old ruins, partner. If I ever get done straightening out all this garbage, that is.
<The anvil is smooth and featureless, save for the alchemical symbol for "Mundus" stamped on the face.>
Don't get many visitors. If you're here for the ruin, best to turn back. No good's come outta that place in  oh, several hundred years. Give or take a decade or so.
Welcome back, warrior. If you have questions about Transitus Shrines, ask.
<The orrery is weathered from exposure to the elements. An etching of the alchemical symbol for Aetherius is barely visible on its base.>
<The fountain contains a murky water that never quite stills. The sculpture above is stamped with the alchemical sign for "Aurbis.">
You come to my realm at the appointed time.
You come to me as a pup, unblooded and weak. What makes you think you are worthy to join my pack?
We'll talk again in Davon's Watch. Look for me at the Fish Stink. It's a little tavern run by Hectur the Fish, down by the docks.nnThat is, unless your bones end up decorating those goblins' huts.
Please, don't hurt me again! I don't want to be eviscerated!
Get out of my face. Unless you want me to mangle yours!
I can't even imagine why I went out there. I thought I saw  my husband of all things. But that couldn't be right. He's not even stationed here. I knew it couldn't be him, and yet  I couldn't resist.
Come to share your latest exploits with us, darling? I fear you'll find Lala and Rock rather hard to impress.
Soon I will be thirsty again. Then I will come find you.

Undaunted! Undaunted! We ate  err  are  eh.nnWhat the blazes are you? Fresh meat, I see. Come to impress and slay, and to drink wine and spill blood. Harken to my words, young one. You will never achieve half the things this old sword has.

As a famous treasure hunter and expert historian, it's no wonder the Mages Guild specifically asked for me to come along. nnI do hope my manservant Stibbons can handle the sights of Coldharbour, though. He's a rather sensitive sort.
The Fighters Guild and the Mages Guild working together? This one never expected to see the day!
The wisdom to work together toward a better understanding of what each arm of the Dominion is doing and what it needs?nnThis is for what I had hoped. This is what seems to have occurred.
Molag Bal's realm is one of the most dangerous and inhospitable places in all of Oblivion. We must not take this invasion lightly.
Coldharbour sounds dreadful. How am I ever going to keep my Lady safe in such a dangerous place?
I shall lead the Fighters Guild into this dreadful realm. We'll make the Lord of Schemes pay for attacking Nirn!
Coldharbour! I don't mind admitting that this old dungeon-delver is probably more excited than she should be! I can't wait to see what kinds of artifacts we can recover.
Lovely day. Much lovelier because of the relative peace and quiet I can enjoy.
I should get back to fishing. <<1>>'s foolishness means we all must work harder. I flatten the spine of disapproval at her actions.nnYou were right to stop her.
So we have you to thank. That's good, you're good. Cracked open my finest fishwine to celebrate.nnThe hardest part is fishing out all the chunks. Ha! Fish. Because it's made from  what was I saying?
I'd rather not get eaten by a daedroth, but I'd dearly love a few of their teeth!
Back again? Do you have questions?
target: Gi tornato? Do you have questions?

source: I don't know about you, but I'm ready to break a few Daedric necks.
Our job will be to help Vanus with the portals. We'll need a lot of them to establish supply lines after we start conquering territory.
I wonder if there are any beautiful ladies in Coldharbour? Or is that a different Daedric Prince?

Others would speak to this better than I, but it seems the tree in the plaza is taking well to its cultivation.nnMy sister said it would never survive leaving Alinor. This, then, would show what she knows.
You're back, I see. Feel free to practice with the weapons. Talk to Jaleel or Marc if you have questions.
I'm ready to cleave some skulls! Do Daedra have skulls? I imagine they do, depending on which type we run into.
Are there any spells or traps in Coldharbour that could turn me into a chicken? I'd just like a fair warning.
There aren't any Goblins in Coldharbour, are there? I have a profound dislike of the vile creatures.
Our alliance owes you a great debt, friend.
Look what the cat dragged in. You kill anything bigger than a spider yet?
Good to see you! I've been promoted since I saw you last, and my sister Ciranya is in good health. I'll give her your best when I see her.
You showed great courage in Wayrest, dealing with the Midnight Union. We'll always be grateful.

I know what you're thinking ,Vestige. You want to thank me for my noble and heroic effort in helping you defeat that treacherous worm, Mannimarco. No need to laud me, though. The world already knows of my brilliance. But you're welcome nonetheless.

I had a bet with Abzag, here. He wagered you wouldn't cough up the coin for that drink. Good thing you didI was supposed to kill you if he was right!nnWell, I wouldn't have killed you. Maybe thrown you across the bar. I'm pretty strong.

Take caution, fragile mortal! You stand before the great Incendion: Master of the Whiteflame, Bearer of the Burning Heart, Kinlord of ancient Sunhold. I could incinerate you with an intake of my breath!nnAnd I have very important work to do.
Inspect my notes, Count Verandis. See if you can find a clue that I overlooked. We need to work together to save the Baroness.
Verandis, you must tell me. Why did this happen to Mother? Of all the people of Shornhelm, why her?nnPlease tell me there's a way to save her. You're powerful. You have to do something!
Well look at this! If it isn't the scamp I sent to clear out a dung heap.nnHah! Going get a little rough for ya scrap? Sure took you long enough!
You are no Undaunted.nnI can imagine your tales of glory. I, too, used to brag about killing dogs and cats.

As an Undaunted, I seek to better myself, but I'm afraid there is little left in this world to challenge me.nnPerhaps there are Daedric realms that are more interesting. A dangerous thought, I suppose.

Can't you see I'm eating?nnYou young scamps always come to Felvyn for advice when I'm in the middle of something. Tell you whatbuy me a drink and I'll give you a tip on making the best use of a blade.
I hear you are giving a hand to the performers. That is great news, maybe my stock won't spoil after all.
The pyrotechnics are a bit much to deal with several times a day, but I find a lot of the first time attendees need a drink after that show.
I can't tell you how glad I am that you found that guy some new stories to tell. I don't think I could've handled any of the old ones one more time.
Brave wayfarer, fellow Undaunted. Welcome to my desert.nnI see you remain unslain. A rarity for an Undaunted!
I have to admit, these bugs seem remarkably well trained. I'm still going to keep my distance though.
Oh. You're back. Guess you weren't eaten by ghosts.

You are Undaunted! This one is glad to see a new member. She has nearly run out of bodies to climb over in her glorious rise to the top.nnYou will help <<1>> with this, yes? <<2>> has been most uncooperative.
Now that the carnival is in full swing, I can't decide what to focus on! The bugs creep me out but the stories and the magic act are so much fun!

I appreciate the drink. Helps keeps the anxieties under control in the depths of a dungeon.nnThis one believes that you are never truly alive unless you are stumbling through a trap or matching wits with a Daedra! So go! Be alive!
I guess the performances aren't so bad. I had no idea you could train insects like you can a dog.

I say, you're awfully quiet for one of the Undaunted. Have you no tongue, or just a dull wit? Ho, ho! Just ribbing you, my friend. Making jokes, sharing laughs! That  that's what we do, right?nnI'm sorry. What was I saying?
Good to see you again. Hranir was just telling us about her latest exploits. Get out there and see if you can match them.
So, you know Seeks-Her-Glory? So do I, if you know what I mean. If you buy me a drink, maybe I'll let you in on a little secret.

Why do you idle, Undaunted?nnGo jump into a cave. Fight a Daedra or something. Seems to be no shortage of those, these days. Like most things, they'll stop moving when you strike their necksthe ones that have necks.
Oh, look at this one! You think you're tough?nnI've seen adventurers like you frozen in terrorat the creatures I've gazed in the eyeand ripped apart. They should call me the Stout! My hands are huge!
Are you drunk, yet? 'Cause I am! Undaunted! Har.nnSo. How are things with you?
Hey, fresh meat. My mouth is dry. Get me a drink, or I'll tell Talisse to ring it out of you.nnShe'll do it. She has big hands.
I hope my friends aren't being too loud. They're friendly people, really. Once you get to know them. They'd be more friendly if you were an Undaunted.
Not afraid of a fight, eh? Good. We need some more honest warriors here.
Son of a troll  I've earned this nap. Don't judge me.

Plenty for an Undaunted to see and do in Coldharbour, my friend. As long as you like walking headlong into danger. There are creatures here that can slay even the dead.nnLet me know if you want to barter for some arms and armor. You'll need them.
Ah, you again. And with every limb intact!nnYou continue to surprise.
I got another one .nnHow many Undaunted does it take to cure the sickness that comes after a night at the tavern? Please, I need to know. By the Egg, I'm going to need to know in the morning.
You must be the one Ram told us about. Let me look at you.nnYou have strong eyes. A strong soul, I'll bet.
By seed and spleen, the Mages Guild is up to something in Selene's Web.
Welcome to the Hollow City, Undaunted. I'm sure you've found that, like Coldharbour itself, there's plenty here to test yourself against.
So nice to talk to a fellow Undaunted. This one is eager to hear about something other than trees.
By the Green Pact, we Bosmer make horrible drinks.nnAt least they get you drunk.

Hello  you! Good to see another Undaunted. I've been drinking my way through all the places Undaunted dwell.nnThe drink here is surprisingly strong. An hour ago, I thought I had become a Khajiit. But I was just looking at one. She set me straight.
A fellow Undaunted!nnIf you need any equipment, you can speak to me. Yours should be well-worn, by now. If you need any leads on adventures  you can also speak to me. I know of a few places.
This is some strong drink. Burns.nnAlmost helps me forget the boredom. I need an adventure.
Getting thrown out of a tavern is a horrible thingyou're deprived of your bar fightsand your bar drinks.nnThe secret is to drink and fightquietly.
Please, don't interrupt. We've much to do to meet the Dominion's expectations in the region.
Our great leaders  are gone, missing. What will we do?
The fight is well and truly lost. Get out of our town, you aren't welcome here.
Who're you? Another Undaunted? A word of warningstay away from <<1>>. I left it days ago, and the cold still burns.
Ah, a fellow Undaunted! My name is Earrona Kneecapper.nnIt's a pleasure to meet you. I hope you find the adventure well in these parts.

Milksop! Come to Velyn Harbor looking for a good bruising? I know just the place. But I can't remember the name.nnPerhaps  perhaps if my mug weren't empty, my memory would improve. Fill my mug. Please.
Well, well, well, look who it is? The second bravest member of the Undaunted.nnCome treat with me, friend! With me and these lovely ladies!
Oh, are you another Undaunted like <<1>>? He is so brave and strong. I could listen to his tales for hours.
Ah, the new blood! You've come far, my friend!
Talisse was just telling us about you. New blood, she called you. Know what would break that unfortunate epithet? Winning a combat tournament.
You are a friend of the Empress of Bone. You will be allowed to live when the Empress destroys this world and replaces it with nothing but bone.

You're not another fool like Felvyn, here, are you? Thinking I'll jump in his bedchamber after a drink? There isn't enough mead in the world for that.nnIsn't enough mead in the world to sate my thirst, either.
I suppose I could construct some Khajiiti statuary, or paint a mural of the Elden Tree.nnI will simply have to speak to some of the dignitaries to see what would fit them best.
The Dominion needs  festivals. Something to bolster faith in the Dominion itself, and celebratory of its formation.nnAnd every good festival needs costumes. Yes, grand pomp for all.

Presently? I am accounting for what goods we have in the embassy, to better monitor future requisitions.nnIf I keep costs low enough, I might be able to hire a replacement for myself, such that I may see some action on my own merit.
You look as fresh as the time I met you, scamp. Does nothing slow you down? I hear you've been making a name for yourself.
This ale's not as good as the grog from the time I ran with Blackheart's crew. But it does its job.
I'm writing my memoirsa record of my great deeds!nnHow about some refreshment, new blood? Hard to write with a parched throat!

I'm looking for work. Know anyone who needs a hauler? I'm real good at breaking down tents, packing them up, and hauling them where they need to be unpacked and pitched.nnAnd don't say carnival. I'm done with carnivals.
I'm terribly sorry, but we our attractions are somewhat limited at the moment. nnPerhaps if you try back in a few weeks?

That's it, then? Seen the world thrice over and none the worse for it, eh? nnYou should be ready for anythingand believe you me, the Daedric Princes never rest. They're always mucking about with something or other!
Greetings, walker! Come, sit by the fire and be welcome!
I don't want to think of the outcome had you not been here.nnYou kept the king safe. You will always be welcome among the Vinedusk Rangers.
The King has been informed of our success. He awaits only your word.
<<1>>  how could this have happened? You had so much greatness within you.nnYour future should have been so very bright.

Things have been a lot quieter around here, lately. It's easier for me to move my adventuring supplies, but there's something I miss about having to break an arm every now and then.nnI think it's the breaking arms part.

I, Boeuf Sterone, have the best food available for miles! How do I know this? Because it is from right here!nnNowhere is it fresher. And it can be so fresh because I no longer need worry about my supply being stolen, so I need not bury it!
Did you know that there was something in those ruins after all? I had no idea! None whatsoever!nnIt's enough to drive me to drink, but I only drink when the sky is blue. Fancy one? A drink, I mean.
I wonder if <<c:1>> is worth all the fuss. I certainly hope the queen isn't wasting her time.nnHmph. And yours.

I don't know you. Fighters Guild facilities here are intended for members only. We've too much to do and too few to do it to spare anything.nnYou should really consider joining us. Our charter benefits all of Tamriel, after all.
Lighting the fire is only part of it, you have to make sure that the guards don't just put it right back out, too!
Do you often storm into the halls of guilds in which you have no membership?nnI assure you, that isn't exactly polite. Unless you're here to join our ranks, of course.

Are you familiar with "handfasting?" I'm not entirely certain what it means, but I'd wager <<1>> and <<2>> will be doing it before the month's end.nnBetween you and I, they've wanted to handfast each other since the day they met.
It's good to have <<1>> back in <<2>>. I thought he would be trapped in <<Ac:3>> until I was old and gray.nnBut that isn't the case. He's here, right now. Safe.

All is well. <<1>> is returned to <<2>>, free of <<3>>'s control. Though I admit, I can hardly call her my apprentice anymore.nnNow, we are more like equals. Different roles for us both, but I welcome the change.
I have failed in my duties. Our foes have stolen the Elder Scroll I guarded. Please, recover it!
Find our Elder Scroll, warrior! Seek out those who have stolen it and kill them for this sacrilege!
I heard you're the newest Briar. I'll let you in on a little secret, I was once a Briar too! But I'm too old to rummage around in the forest these days.
Don't just stand therethe Elder Scroll of Ghartok has been stolen! Help your comrades recover it!
You passed the trial? You should speak with Lereluin. My husband is always pleased to meet new Briars.
I am to take Glaras' place when she steps down. I have much to learn and many years to grow before that happens.
I wish I could have stormed <<1>> myself, but I swore my strength to my thane's side. I must resort to indirect measures to protect her.
Hurry to <<1>>. You'll find <<2>> entrenched at the gate to <<3>>.
Be careful in the barrow. Our ancestors went to great lengths to protect their dead.
He went further into the barrow. Be careful. I'll be fine on my own. Put an end to this, and find me in Ivarstead after you do. I owe you a debt for helping me.
I will do a better job of looking after my older brother. He thinks age brings wisdom. Hah!

I call this a successful day. We beat Reezal-Jul and we saved the lovely Captain Janeve.nnYou know what would make it even better? If I can convince all these lovely ladies to join me for a drink at the nearest tavern.
What am I going to do? I have to clear all this rubbish before the end of my shift. Ambassador's orders, they said!
It is no use. The High Elves care nothing about their promises to the Khajiit. Nothing will change, no matter how much we shout!
I thought you were on our side! I mean, after all you did for us  er, I mean . Never mind.
You're back! Not a moment too soon, all this mead is making me soft around the middle.nnPlease tell me it's time to smash things?
You've returned! My blade is ready. Hunting bandits and enraged wildlife is a poor substitute for traveling with you.
I had hoped you'd return. I enjoyed adventuring with you again. Perhaps you have need of me once more?
Heed my words, friend. There is more to Montclair's betrayal than the Baron and the Countess know.nnI suggest you proceed with caution when you enter the upper city.
So many things to do! Adusa doesn't have enough hours in the day.nnPerhaps you could lend a hand, my friend. You help Adusa, yes?
The brothers and I appreciate your help, my friend! I know this job might have been a little rough, but we're getting better with every contract. You'll see!

You're the only one who isn't a member of this group. Perhaps you will speak truly. The contract specifies they must do the work promptly and effectively. nnI'm not sure what happened, to be honest. Did they do anything worth paying for?
Thanks to you, our reputation remains intact.
I feel better knowing someone is going to try to help the mayor. And I'll go make my report and send more troops this way.
I thank you. Sithis willing, it is not too late to stop the Dominion.
I gave you fair warning. Whether or not you decide to listen, that's up to you.
Did you tell the truth? What are you thinking?

You're smart. Working for the Ring of Daggers has two great benefits. nnFirst, we reward our friends generously. Second, we don't worry about trials and laws and silly things like that. Get Althen to Hoarfrost Downs and he will pay for what he did.
Sagabar and I were just making bets on whether you'd return.nnLooks like Sagabar's a two-time loser. Did you do it then? Did you kill Gavendien?
You brought Gavendien to justice, eh? I'm glad.nnYou know, if you were ever interested in becoming a deputy to the constable. I'm just saying  the job's open.
I hope you made that man suffer. For what he did to Mondorie, he deserved a brutal end. nnDamn bandits. Now I'm just hoping my horse comes home.
Oh. Hello, there. You must be new in town .nnI'm sorry, but the jewelry shop is closed for today. Constable Gavendien's orders.
I sure do love fishing. Fishing is fun. I could fish all day.
My husband and the others did what they thought was best. Who knew that dreadful Gavendien would go back on his word?
Poor Rubyn! How will he ever get along without his mother?
Poor mother. She didn't deserve this fate.

Have you come to join us for the final push, Lieutenant? We are all that's left of the King's Guard, but at least we'll take a few Orcs down with us.nnAs soon as we see an opening, we're charging into that breach down there.
I guess this is what I deserve. Very well. I accept my fate.
<The wine's aroma makes your mouth water in anticipation.>
I can't believe you recruited Julien. If I could eat my dagger, I would.nnI'm really embarassed. I couldn't manage to get a single recruit, and you come behind me and get all three.
I've told you everything. Let's not do anything hasty, all right.

Well, my friend, it appears that the book is real and not part of Lleraya's illusion. I believe it will be of great help to us in the trials ahead.nnThat said, I have much research to do. Ancient Ayleid isn't my native language, you know.

Ah! A stranger in town. I was just saying how we needed more strangers around here. You know, walking around, bothering people who are just trying to do an honest day's work.nnIs that the kind of stranger you are, friend?
Leave me alone.

The army waits for my signal, out beyond the farms. I want to keep the damage to Northpoint to a minimum. Marching soldiers have a habit of destroying persons and property, even when they're trying to be careful.
I am grateful for your help. I'll steel myself and get out of here shortly.
It's nice out here. No more crawling around crypts, no more undead. No more really heavy armor. No more preaching about Arkay. Nope. No more. I'm done.
This one is glad you are with the Guild at this difficult time. Bear with us, adept.

Go. I need to remain and tend to Darien.nnHe claimed the bloodfiends bit him, but I found nothing but bruises and shallow scratches on his body. I see no signs of the vampire's curse, but I want to watch him to make sure he's all right.
Look around you. Does it look like we have time for idle chatter?
So tell me, what news from Verandis? Has Count Ravenwatch's research finally borne fruit?
Baron Montclair must pay for his crimes. I plan to see to it. Personally.nnI shall gather my troops and prepare to ascend the Doomcrag.
I'm ready. No, I am more than ready! The time has come to put Baron Montclair down like the crazed dog he has become.
Remember, the man that Montclair was is gone now. He no longer exists. Only the monster remains.nnSo don't hold back. Keep him busy until I can join you.
This seems to be <<1>>. She was concerned  she writes about Arlie's sad smiles. Missing me, no doubt. She brought Arlie flowers  and then, they went to the windmill. Oh dear!
I'll miss <<1>>. She was a good  friend.
With Federic back it's going to be harder to keep Arlie's attention. That doesn't mean I won't try, though! My days of sitting idly by are over!
Our home is yours to stay in, for as long as you like. It's the least we can do.
Now that Federic's returned for good, everything will be right again!

Don't worry. I'm not going to try to skip town or anything. If I wanted to do that, I'd have just spit in your eye and stabbed you in the stomach, and gone along my merry way.nnI'm coming  when I feel like it.
Verandis is waiting for you at the Lorkrata ruins. So, what are you still doing here staring at me?

Verandis claims he has a plan to vanquish Montclair, but he hasn't been forthcoming with the details.nnStill, he's dealt honorably with us so far. I'm willing to let him take the lead at this point in the campaign.
I'm going to share a secret with you, Adept. I've always felt a bit of a fraud. My teachers always told me how gifted I was, how brilliant, but I never really believed them.
I had a feeling I might see you here. I wasn't sure if I was ready to face you. nnYou saw me in such a dark moment. But they taught me how to control the hunger.
Wherever she is, I wonder if Heloise is watching all this. I hope she's at peace.
What are you waiting for? Get on your horse and get to the starting line!
You faced down Montclair and lived to tell about it! I'm envious, you know.

I saw you over there at the stocks talking to Martin. Does that fool still think I'm coming to his rescue? He's like a babe in the woods. nnI told him not to wear those fancy boots. It's not my fault he wouldn't listen.
We did it! Now let's get out of here. We can talk more when we get outside.

Look at these peopleyou'd never guess hundreds of people recently died in a terrible war. nnLet them have a moment of happiness, though. You and I know it was only because of Verandis' sacrifice that any of us are still here.

You saved our family and the kingdom, so I guess that makes us doubly in your debt. nnAnd if High King Emeric can choose a new ruler for Rivenspire, my daughter should be able to choose her  preferences as well.
A new ruler for Shornhelm. This is a huge moment for Rivenspire.nnWe should all be honored to witness such a moment.
Can you believe it? She still won't make up her mind!
Hi there. You know, I just noticed that you have really pretty eyes.nnOh, I mean  not that I'm flirting with you or anything. Not unless you want me to.
You know, I think I've decided it's more fun when you don't choose  even when you have to. It's fun having everyone waiting for you to make up your mind.
Go on. Don't wait for me.nnBut thank you, though. For, you know. Helping Verandis. Thanks.
Check with the Baron and see if he has anything to report while I consider our next move.
What word of the Mage and her aspects? We can't afford to let the Serpent control another Celestial Guardian.

I would stand here and drink myself to death, but I can't even afford to do that!nnMy mother told me that if I became a poet, I would starve to death. When I wrote a book, I thought I had proven her wrong. But it's come to nothing!
And like a faithful hound, you follow on the heels of your master. Should I have you sit? Roll over? Beg? Perhaps later.nnFor now, why don't you stand over there and wait for my blessing to begin.
That statue  it's so cold. It feels like the dead of winter.

I can't tell you how much I appreciate you convincing me to enlist. I've come to realize that this is what I was born to bea soldier.nnI also met some soldiers who served under my father. They spoke highly of him. I hope I can honor his memory.

If you decide you want to leave, talk to the captain. I can't think of any reason at all for us to stay here. nnI can deal with thieves, pirates, and all manner of vagabonds, but I'm not getting near any undead.

A finer group of soldiers never served in the Shornhelm Guard. Julien and Shuga have both turned out to be valiant warriors.nnAnd Martin, that young man is a natural leader. He's a war hero now, too. He saved dozens of lives in battle the other day.

Ah! You're one who killed that old skeever Dark Elf I was seeing! What was his name again ? No matter. He's ancient history now. nnI'm sharing a tent with Julien these days, if you catch my meaning. For the time being, at least.

If it isn't Mara's messenger in the flesh! You really saved my love-life. Looking back, I can't imagine what I ever saw in Guendeline. nnKhalisah. Now that's the woman of my dreams! It warms my heart to think she's waiting for me back at home.
So you're headed out to the desert too? That works. I got some timber to sell there in Sentinel.nnI sure as Oblivion better make more off this trip than the price of your fare.
Any time is a good time for a mug of port.
You know what really chaps my breeches? Montclair's troops stole a whole bunch of the weapons I just completed. nnI'll be working for weeks to catch up!

This was once a sacred place devoted to the worship of Akatosh. Now, these sand devils have defiled and destroyed it. It must be cleansed. I plan to call out the Celestial who did this and deal with him.
If you're seeking passage to Ebonheart and points beyond, you'll just have to wait.
I see now what the burnt bones told me. Pain, suffering. And hope. The last bone means hope.
Your help has been invaluable, my friend, but I fear that Craglorn's troubles are far from over.
Bad time for visitors. Lots of omens. Caravans being slaughtered. Hope you're not here to see the sights.
You're back! I was beginning to worry for your safety. Did you find the amulet? Tell me everything that happened!
I'm glad Holgunn sent you. Kyne knows we could use a little luck.nnSpeak to Netapatuu if you think you can help.
Please, do not interrupt me. I must open this for you.
Welcome to the Ouside Inn, traveler! We're the only inn ouside of Elden Root itself, hence the name.
Shornhelm has a new ruler? Well, it's about time! Unless that highfaluting High King wants to spend all his time in Rivenspire, we need someone here who can make decisions and get things done.
The High King actually named a single ruler for Shornhelm? Amazing! It's good to have a proper ruler on our throne again.
I can't believe they gave the crown to that silly young woman! She isn't half as worthy as the brave and handsome Baron Dorell.
I can't believe they gave the crown to that overbearing, pompous bore! He isn't half as worthy as the brave and beautiful Countess Tamrith.
I hear we have our own king again. Well, we know how well that worked out the last time.
So the High King gave the crown to Baron Dorell? Well, that figures. Fancy pants Emeric was never going to award rulership to a woman. That's just not the way it's done.
Greetings and welcome! Do I smell the distinct aroma of ink and parchment? Perhaps an ancient scroll? Or is it a musty tome?
It's a good thing you showed up. I wasn't looking forward to rolling down this hill, trying to get to Kragenmoor before the Daggers.

Any knowledge of enemy tactics is a good thing. Perhaps we can use their little trick against the Covenant. Or get the Goblins to attack their camps. nnI'll leave that to Holgunn. Me, I don't want to ever see another spider again.
Thanks again for retrieving my wares, traveler. I'll make for Kragenmoor soon enough.
I will keep an eye on the barrier, in case anything changes. You go find Walks-In-Ash!
Smell the ash on the wind? That's the wind of change, set to scour the Daggers from our shores.
I apologize for not being able to speak much at the moment.nnMy lovely Celan and I had a rather  rough trip most recently.
Blood for the Pact, eh? Ha ha ha!
Good thing I'm such a patient woman, so dedicated to my oath. Otherwise I'd be wondering out loud why our commander has gone insane.
Ysgramor guide your blade! Hah!

Don't let the name fool you. Ash Mountain isn't a giant pile of ashes. It's much lovelier than that. It's a looming, active volcano. You can smell the brimstone from here.nnSounds compelling, doesn't it?
Still-Water and I have been partners for years. Just business, but you get to know a person after all that time in the wilds. Damn it. I'm going to miss that scaley bastard.
<The Argonian's body is just starting to cool.>
No Hagraven? I was sure there was a Hagraven? Then what was doing all that blasted screeching?
I'll wait here until you return. I want to be around when my drunken spouse gets back so we can discuss how I apparently remind him of a screeching Hagraven.
Almost finished with this row. Crops aren't looking too bad. Considering everything that's happened.
If I were you, I'd look for him near rats. He's got quite an appetite.
By the Three, Argonians sure take their time. You'd think he was an artist, the way he treats this farm.
Smells delicious. I love Dawn's cooking. I count our blessings that they decided to stay and work for us after the Pact.
I'm working up an old family recipe for later. It's so nice to be appreciated, you know?
Damned well. After the volcanos started acting up, it's gone completely dry. I'm sure I'll be running back and forth to Kragenmoor more than I like.
Now that that's over with, we should return to Camp Tamrith and let <<1>> know that the task is complete.
What happened? I heard a commotion and was about to send a few of the guard to investigate.
What happened? I blacked out.
You're doing me a tremendous service, friend. Those soldiers have been sending couriers to ask what's going on for weeks now. I know they'll be happy to get this dispatch.
Time to crack open another jug of Ungorth. Only thing that makes this bearable.
I wouldn't mind having someone like you on my staff. You fight like a Daedra and have the courage of a dozen guards. If you ever want a real job, come back and see me.
<This is Aera's log book. In it she keeps the names of all Worm Cult agents she has brought to justice.>
I don't know if you delivered my offering to Pariah Abbey or not, but something made a difference. My heart has been lighter in recent days.
May Azura's blessing be with Sergeant Oorga, and with you.
<This massive construct stands dormant, since it is still missing some crucial gears and pistons. An etched panel bears an inscription.>
I'm just going to wait here and rest until the healers come to collect me.
If I thought the Three gave a damn about me, I'd pray for you. Instead I'll wish you good luck and a sharp blade.
I'm already thinking of what to tell the House elite at the next party in Mournhold. I'm trying to decide how thrilling to make the tale. You understand, I'm sure.
Good luck. The Montclair family is one of the oldest in Rivenspire. If they think they can win this conflict, it's a good bet they have something up their sleeves.

Welcome to Hoarfrost Downs. It may just be the dreariest hamlet in Rivenspire, but don't let that scare you away.nnActually, this entire kingdom is rather dreary, isn't it? Nevermind. I sense you've brought something for me.
Hail, stranger! I don't recognize you. You're not a member of the guild, are you? By Ysgramor's beard, why not?
Please, don't walk away. Don't ignore me. I really need your help. This blasted war has been devastating to us common folk.nnCan you spare a few pieces of gold for a poor beggar?
Tell the Baron we're waiting on him. If he needs us, we'll come running.
You have answered well and true. Through the gates, you may proceed.
They lied to us! The Maulborn  they're not trying to help. They're monsters!
I don't believe it. This is all some sort of trick, perpetrated by the houses or the Tribunal. The Maulborn can't be responsible for the plague. I simply refuse to accept that.
You can't restart while others are still inside the raid.
The Fighters Guild is here to serve! You know how it is. Hah!
We're proud to be here. No matter what the locals say, the Guild is here to help!
Your word is unquestioned. I am here to command.nnThough my blow caused Belronen's death, it was set in motion by another hand. I will aid you in discovering the source of this duel, if you will it.
My lord, the life of one such as Vamen bears no comparison to Belronen Telvanni. Yes, I sought to root corruption from the temple by poisoning that pile of scrib jelly. I'd do it again!

I did nothing but provide opportunity for a heretic to destroy himself. The act of dueling anyone within the temple would undo him. It's only fitting the fetcher did so with the tools I presented, and with such finality.
Good to have a roof here. Fighters Guild camps aren't always so well equipped, you know? Even if we do have to share with the Mages.
Be wary. The Wilderking's influence ebbs, even here in Greenheart. nnThe spirits of the forest are confused and angryeven my brethrenthey will attack you with no provocation.
Who are you, then? Are you with our esteemed guests, or were you hoping to take shelter under the Skald-King's skirts?
Eagles advance, traveler! And may the Green watch and keep you.
What wonders you will see in the halls of Shad Astula. Oh, how I envy you! To experience it all again for the first time againthat would be marvelous!
Don't hold rudeness against the royals. It's like the scorpion, you know? It's in their nature.
I'll get my brother out of here. Thank you for helping me find him.nnI know you can take care of yourself. Just make sure you give these Maulborn a taste of their own bad medicine. For me.
Have you found the pages of my book?
Oh, hello. Do I know you?
The longer you delay, the longer Hazazi must stand here. Go!
Hail, friend. I trust you're gathering an impressive amount of Daedra heads? nnRumor has it the God of Brutality has taken notice of your handiwork.
I hear the buzz of fungus growing .
You did it! You found all my missing family members!

The Bramblebreach village is just south of Marbruk. Hazazi is there. He likes to complain, but he's a good soldier. He just needs someone with a more sophisticated negotiation style. nnAnd by the time you get back, Raz will have a lead on the staff!
Thank goodness you came when you did.
Talk to my sister. She's got something to say.
Did you free the captives?
Don't come any closer. I don't want you to get the plague.
Don't touch anything! And try not to breathe too deeply. The affliction, it's everywhere! Everywhere!
Please  more curative  I need more curative .
Welcome to our guild hall. It's more of a bungalow than a hall, but you get the idea. Have you come seeking membership in the Mages Guild?
Did you manage to close all of the portals?
Thank you for helping the Serk, my friend. The town would have been lost without you.nnStill, you shouldn't get too close to me. Just in case.
Forgive the sorry state of our facilities, but we're still reeling from the attack on Haven.nnHave you come seeking membership in the Mages Guild?
I told you to sod off.
Welcome to the Elden Root Mages Guild Hall! Impressive, yes? Makes the one in Firsthold look like something of a broom closet. Don't repeat that.nnHow can I help you?
A word of caution: if you request a post in the Wood Elf frontier, be prepared to eat liver. At least I think it's liver.nnBut waityou're not part of the Mages Guild, are you?

Don't mind the smell. I think one of those creatures relieved itself on the bookshelf. Charming, yes?nnHopefully none of the tomes were damaged. Their loss would be a great tragedy for the Mages Guild.
You look like someone that knows how to handle themself in a fight. We could use the help.
Did you heal the injured?
If you're seeking the Mages Guild, you've come to the right place. If you're looking for more brutish endeavours, I suggest you speak with someone on the other side of the hall.
Carpets to clean, scrolls to reorganize . Wood Orcs. Thugs, the lot of them.nnBut enough of our troubles. Have you come to join the Mages Guild?
This seems like an odd place for the Mages Guild to set camp, yes? Well, we don't spend all our time in musty old libraries. This swamp pulses with arcane powerwe'd be fools to ignore it.

I spent several hours watching the Wood Orcs and evaluating their weaknesses.nnAs a whole, their strength is in numbers. As long as you don't take on the entire camp, you should be fine. The chieftain's the one you have to watch out for.
Find those ingredients quickly.nnI must stay here to attend to the patient.
Auri-El smiles down on us. Mara's heart beats in your chest. And the bravery of Stendarr guides your hand.

I suspected they might choose to fight. They are not the first clan to seek to settle in this place, and sadly, they will likely not be the last.nnHopefully, next time, we might convince them to leave in peace.
Auri-El smiles down on us. Mara's heart beats in your chest. And the bravery of Stendarr guides your hand.

By the Three, these formulae don't look right at all.nnI was just collating these volumesthough I hardly see the point. The Mages Guild's expectations are very high. You'll learn that lesson well if you choose to join us.
I knew we could count on you. Just keep your wits about you. The Stormfists possess an unusual amount of cunning for a gang of common thugs.
Welcome to our completely ludicrous "guild hall." If it was up to me I wouldn't be herebut where our banner hangs, so too must a magister.
Good to see you back again, Adept. The Guild is stronger with you at our side.
Is there anything the Mages Guild can do for you my friend?
I don't know how to thank you. Without your help, the Maulborn would have destroyed the Serk.
There's no time for idle chit-chat right now. If you want to stay, you'll have to be quiet.
Good luck finding lodging! With so many petitioners, the inn's turning people away.

I must admit, your help was invaluable. It may not be a cure, but I can certainly use this suppressant to slow the progress of the plague to a crawl.nnHopefully, that will give me or the healers in Mournhold time to develop a proper curative.
Waiting is the hardest part. But if we trust in the Three, I'm certain everything will turn out fine.
I'm as busy as a skeever in a trash pit! Do you need something?
Lovely day, isn't it? Ate a bit too much at dinner, though. Haven't had any of Greenshade's snails in a long, long time.nnGo on in! There's probably some left over. We always share what we have.
Please, leave me alone. I don't want to talk about what happened here.
Welcome to our hall, fellow member. Please make yourself at home.

Undead? Ha. These are no rotting draugr or mindless skeletons. But it's true. They can't hardly be called living, either.nnUntie these bonds and help me stop them. I'll tell you what I can when I'm free.
I can't tell you how flattered I am that you offered your assistance, but please, don't worry about me.nnI can clean my own fruit.
I hope you and Gelvin aren't going to disappoint us. The Daggers are counting on your good judgment, friend.
Comrade, welcome back. Remember to keep your blade clean, now.
A real Celestial right here in the observatory. It's incredible. What a chance to learn! Do you think she'd obliterate me if I touched her?
Come, mortal. Do a favor for this poor, weary spirit.
Don't let that Saravith talk you into anything. The fact that her spell worked at all and there weren't any strange side effectswell, that was just plain lucky, if you ask me.
You were the one? The one that helped the alchemist? Oh, thank you!nnMy wife hasn't been cured, but at least the plague won't continue to get worse as long as the suppressant holds out.
Greetings. Have you come to the Ashlands seeking glory and honor? The caverns of Stonefalls hold treasure. And danger. And death. nnAhem. Have you heard of them? The Armature? Emberflint?
Old Sorel no longer has any use for these things. Make like the wind and blow, or we shall be forced to exchange harsh words.
Old Sorel Tedas had good taste, don't you think? Too bad what happened to him. He was always nice to me. Liked to talk about politics and the weather.
Old Sorel takes care of us, even now that he's gone. Just don't mention you saw us to the house Elves. They wouldn't understand.
I feel terrible .

Who knew that the job of a town consul would keep me so busy? I've barely had a chance to have a proper meal, let alone relax with a good book.nnBut thanks to you and Nilyne, the suppressant should buy us the time we need to defeat this plague.
Brave little scrib, do you know how to swim?
Aerona has really stepped up as town consul while her brother recovers. He'd better watch out. She may actually be better at the job than he is!

I'm glad you and Aerona didn't give up on me. I'm feeling much better. But Nilyne says her potion has only suppressed the plague, not cured it.nnIf you find a way to beat this plague, make sure you send word to us. And thanks for helping my town.

I have my work cut out for me. I need to make enough of the suppressant to treat everyone in the Serk. And then I have to continue trying to find an actual cure.nnDamn the Maulborn and their Llodos plague! Damn them to Oblivion and back!
Friend! I'm so glad to see you again.nnI've been keeping up my end of the bargainwith Verandis' help, of course.
I can't believe Verandis is really gone.nnI'm not sure what we're going to do without him, but we promised to continue the work he started here. That's the best way to honor his memory.
Thank you for sparing me. I may never be my true self again, but I can still serve Rivenspire.
<A slightly overcooked turkey leg, suspiciously uneaten.>

What? Yes? Ah. I see, a traveler. Have you come to the Ashlands looking for profit? House Dres applauds your efforts. nnIn fact, we're planning to exploit two new resources soon. Have you heard of the Hightide Hollow? Or Mephala's Nest?
Speak with care as you talk to Helgana, traveler. Her injuries are too great. Her soul will soon be with her honored ancestors in Sovngarde. nnI am just here to see her on her way.
Please, come  come closer. You need to know. nnThe Covenant  portal.
Thank you again. You have no idea how much your generosity has helped us out.nnThree watch over you!
Erunor is young for a caretaker, it must be hard on his wife.
Nilyne's suppressant will hold the plague at bay. It has to.nnI really don't want to pack up and move my wagon again.
Nilyne says that vile potion she made me drink will keep the plague from turning me into a zombie.nnI guess it didn't taste that bad, after all.
I'm glad we decided to come to the Serk. The town alchemist has been very helpfuleven if she keeps trying to get me to drink sour milk tea. I never developed a taste for the stuff.
My father meant well, bringing us here, but the Maulborn deceived us all. I fear this plague is going to take us all.
I thought all the guests were in the garden already! My apologies!
Do you see them? Do you see the flowers? They're beautiful  simply beautiful.
Whatever is going on up there, I pray you can resolve it quickly. Good luck.
Mara grant you speed and mercy!
Auri-el watch over you!
Have you heard? The alchemist has come up with a suppressant. It isn't a cure, but at least it gives us a fighting chance against this damn plague.
Quite an event, isn't it? All the best guests, the wine flowing freely .
My wife  I think the plague has rattled her mind. I pray that she recovers, but I fear the damage may be too severe.
Thanks for your help. Make sure you tell my cousin that I'm all right. If you head south, you won't be able to miss the Serk.nnTell her I'll return home as soon as I'm able.
Well, this job was underwhelming.nnYou ended up doing all the work! Maybe next time I can actually join you, eh?
So Dethisam and Aerona were right? The Maulborn are nothing more than  common swindlers! I am so angry right now I feel like knocking heads together!
Ah, good to see a fresh face. We villagers can get tired of just looking at each other after a hundred years.
You have done well to stop Tarish-Zi from gathering his cursed army of Anka-Ra.
I'm shaking all over inside. To be attacked in one's own home ! Valenwood is not as safe as it once was, I fear.
Not many of us work with stone. These foundations always need a bit of adjustment when we return.
Good thing we came back! I'm almost out of rotmeth. Nothing like a good dose of local fauna to bring out the best in it, I always say!
Sorry, can I help you? I'm a bit busy here. The Master has given me much to do, and little time to do it.
Oh, a fellow adventurer, eh? I'm surprised to see you here. I barely managed to sneak past those Iron Orcs. I didn't expect them to have gathered here so quickly.
Talk some sense into that old wizardif you can!

I heard some men talking in the marketplace. They claimed the Iron Orcs are stirring in the northern hills, like they're preparing for something big. I hope it isn't true. We have enough to worry about right now.
The Artisan, finally caught! Now what will the gossip be about, no?
I heard you brought that Imperial back to the Star-Gazers! Is he as good as rumors claim? I'll have to invite him for some mead at the Crossroads. He's got to have some tales worth hearing!
You stand before me, not wounded and defeated, but proud and courageous.nnYou have overcome the trials! But what happened to the betrayer?
I'm already beginning to record the events that have transpired. How exciting! nnAs far as we know, this is the first time a Celestial has lingered so long among mortals like this.
If I'd had the Artisan's skill, I would have used it to make enough gold to live somewhere else.
Barkeep Frina believes that mug is good luck. With the Yokudans at our gates, we need all the good fortune we can get. Be sure to return it to her.

You'll want to swing by the smithy with that hammer when you can.nnMilrin's as fine a craftsman as there is under the stars, but he's denser than an anvil, and we need his armors to equip our guard against the Yokudans.
Take that book right across the way there to the Architect. I'm sure he'll get some more crazy ideas he'll want to sketch down for me to build out soon enough.
Is it really so late? Please, hurry to the fountain and tell Juliana I'll be there soon. Just head back towards the main hall.nnTell her to wait for me! I'll be there soon!
At least I know now that Alexam didn't forget about me. He just never made it here.nnMaybe I can rest easy now. Thank you for that.
Knowledge for knowledge. That is my price.nnWhat have you brought me, Seeker?
Thank you for your trust and your faith in me. I won't forget it.
Leaving so soon? Tell all your friends about us! Conversation tends to become rather stale down here without a steady supply of fresh faces.
I knew we shouldn't have hired that Bosmer. That was just asking for trouble.nnIn any case, how may I help you? Need to make a deposit or withdrawal?
Sister-of-Wind will recover. Breathing normal, body healing. Her dreams were tainted by the injuries.nnAlways happy when I help another. Always remember the ones I couldn't save.

Then what are you still talking to me for? Get to Hel Ra Citadel before all the good fighting is done.nnAnd if you see those fools who left me behind, tell them I said to go to Sovngarde. And not to enjoy themselves.
Divines guide your sword-arm and let your spells strike true. Slay Abelazar the betrayer and grant rest to the Sword-Disciples.
Need passage between Auridon and Grahtwood? I have a deal with some privateers. They'll take us across the Lane, free of charge.nnSay the word and I'll row us out to meet them.
<The ancient relic on this pedestal thrums with power. As you approach, the distinct taste of salt floods your mouth.>
May the light of Aldmeris guide you and may this whole nightmare be put to rest quickly  and with the least possible suffering.

I have been a soldier all my life, but never have I seen such a dreadful turn of events. Prince Naemon? An army of undead?nnIt's fortunate Camoran sent the Vinedusk Rangers, because there are simply too few Dominion troops to defend the city.
Please. Whatever it takes. Find the captain.

I am sorry for the deception. I was uncomfortable dealing with a Daedric Prince. And, I admit it, I was afraid.nnI have since embraced my role. Hermaeus Mora's curiosity is insatiable, but his knowledge reaches beyond mortal understanding.
I wish I could tell you more, but it will fall to you to uncover the Serpent's plan. I will answer what I can.
Sorry about not following you in there. Nereids have a reputation for controlling the minds of any mortal that crosses their path. They make my skin crawl.
I have given you all that I am willing for the deeds done here.nnYou must stop the Yokudans at all cost. Their presence lingers here no more. Now it is up to you to stop them.
Greetings, Adept. Good to see you in person. I am Vanus Galerion, head of the Mages Guild you so ably serve. I have need of your assistance.
You found the cups, I'll give you the first drink.
Ah, you're back. You have the meat pies, yes?
Good luck. Wherever your travels take you next, know that you have the power of Sheogorath to make you strong.
Ah, you return! And with news of the Maulborn. Tell me what the s'wits are up to now.
Ah. The Trial of the Arena. It was always my favorite. A beautiful dance of teamwork, patience, and skill.nnAbelazar the betrayer beat it with such grace. His movements were like silk.
Navigating the hidden path requires faithin one's senses and in one's masters.nnAbelazer the betrayer made a mockery of both. He was not what he seemed.
The trial of martial knowledge required cooperation and patience. Initiates needed to work together to gather the books. nnAbelazer tricked the others into helping him bring about their demise.
I never thought I would see this day. And so soon! Abelazar the betrayer is dead. Thanks to you.
Surely you are a great champion of Sentinel, Wayfarer. Your deeds are known to the whole of the court and the spirits beyond the shore.
What else can you take from me? My entire journey is wasted because of you!
What do you want now? My claws?nnNo, for they are worth nothing. Forget this one's jest, yes?
I won't report you to the guards. Out of courtesy, you understand? Not because I'm frightened.
Mercenaries next time. Strong ones. That's what I'll bring.
Vivec's quivering backside  again? You already took my gold. What next, the lint in my coin purse?

Making sure the Staff of Magnus is safe in Marbruk is the queen's top priority right now.nnBe patient with Captain Sarandil. Raz has heard he is  proud of his city. You are the queen's envoy in this, so be on your best behavior.
Ah, another intrepid traveler visiting our rustic outpost.
Ah, my friend! My children are healthy thanks to your benevolence! Their bellies swell thanks to your generosity!nnBut times have not smiled on us since, I fear. Our gold dwindles to a scarce sum .

Oh, my friend! Thank Mara I've found you once more!nnDastards! Miscreants of the very worst cut! As soon as you left they were upon mebeating me, taking the gold you so kindly gave me to feed my poor, starving children!
Ah, walker! The coin you gave me has served me well, but I've, ah  lost it. To the unfeeling ravages of time, yes?nnI mean, bandits! The same bandits as before!
We meet again, I'm afraid. Your gold did much to fill my belly, but the moon turns and its hollows gape wide once more.
Ah, the burr-sap! Catch my heel again?
You've saved us from an incredible embarassment. The Fighters Guild needs people like you.
I represent the Fighter's Guild, and induct new members into our ranks.
Spare a sword-arm for the Fighters Guild? We need all can get. Axe-, stave-, and hammer-arms are also acceptable.nnBow-arms, too. I guess.
As far as I'm concerned, the Fighters Guild should join you. I'll waive all requirements for entry, if you're interested in being a part of something bigger.
You can find the Dominion's best warriors in our ranks. This is why you should join us!
The lizards here say Hissmir is a great trial. Passing it makes you  more lizardy.nnHa! I'll tell you what a real trial iskilling Daedra. Join the Fighters Guild and see for yourself.
Our banners represent the blood of members such as you. You strengthen us with your every effort.
You don't look like a pirate! I mean, unless you're trying to look like a pirate. I'm not familiar with the latest fashion.nnYou should join the Fighters Guild. Even if you're a pirate.
Please. You need to get that order to my brother in Mournhold as soon as you can.
Go talk to <<1>>. He's at the camp near the old ruins.
If you happen to run into my sister, let her know that I'll make sure she gets her order. Somehow.nnJust don't tell her what I really do here. It would break her heart.
Please. Go to Honrich Tower as soon as you can. This is serious.nnI've been studying under Elfriede for ten years and I've never seen her so worried about anything.
I'm impressed my apprentice actually found you. Maybe he's smarter than I give him credit for?nnWell, I don't want to be hasty. We'll see if he can get himself back here in one piece.
The help you provided is most appreciated. Perhaps our paths will cross again.

If there's any chance Nahlia is alive, we have to find her.nnLook at the scroll and see if you can make anything out of it. I couldn't go after her on my own, but now that you're here, we have to try.

Some of our researchers disappeared a few days ago in the city wing. And the crypt wing  well, we've stayed away from that one. Terrible sounds emanate from there.nnI guess what I'm saying is, be careful. It's not just the water that's dangerous.
I hear you defeated Yamanu-ko and her apprentices. nnIt will take a long while for the city to get back to normal, but at least it's our city once more.

I'm relieved that the city is safe, but I can't say I'm glad that Yamanu-ko's gone.nnShe taught me everything I know about magic. She always warned me about the temptations of power. For her to fall like this .
Without your help, I don't know what would have happened!
<Symbols appear next to pictures of a man instructing a centurion. This could be instructions on how one teaches a centurion to act on its own.>
You've done well. Craglorn is safe, for now. I will remain behind, in case this place becomes unstable again.
Thank you, my friends. Nerien'eth was no longer the man I knew.nnPerhaps he never was.
I can bring this barrier down, it's just going to take time!
First he berates us for imagined slights, then he kills and tortures us. All that I might be able to forgive  but daedra? nnWhat was he thinking?

It's a fascinating ritual  in a hypothetical sense. nnSplitting away the less powerful parts of yourself, to leave only the strongest aspects of your soul? I'm not saying I would try it, but it is fascinating.

I protested against the bargain. I did not trust the salvation Shada promised.nnFor my troubles, Shada cursed me twice. I was forced to drink the water, but to remain conscious, watching as my people slowly went mad under Shada's influence.
I'm happy you found her. That you saved her.nnBut  I feel sad, too. The woman I  thought she wasshe never existed, did she? In a way, I feel like Hara never came back at all. Maybe I'm being selfish.
You've defeated me. My life is in your hands.
Don't just stand there. I know there is some way you can make yourself useful. If nothing else, just go and kill some of those damn Worms.
I've told you all I know. You need to bind the monarch atronachs before we can understand what's happening.

With the Treeminder dead, we could kill this Hist, end its story here and now. Or simply leave it. Without the Treeminder, it cannot see, cannot feel. I would inflict both, if I could.nnMy sisters were granted no mercy. I will grant none.
I didn't expect to see a friendly face. You are a friend, are you not?
Do not take Zal'ik lightly. Even as he rests now, his power is beyond most have ever faced.nnIf you manage to succeed, I will find you at the end of the caves.
Our friend is losing all the things that make her her.nnI have tried every known cure for madness, delirium, and memory loss I know. I am afraid all is lost!
Use the Gem of Aetherial Command to bind the two remaining monarch atronachs.nnThe flame monarch can be found within the halls of Molavar. The stone monarch is near Balamath.

Servants of the Serpent hired the feared Greycloak mercenaries to capture Kelmen Locke.nnThe merceneries hold him in a place called Haddock's Market. When they learn all they can, they plan to hand Kelmen over to the Serpent. We need to rescue him.
Find Kelmen Locke hiding among the bandits. Do not let the atronachs remain in the Serpent's control.
This is very bad news.nnThe Serpent used the monarchs and their power to create a new atronachone with the ability to take on the elements of other atronachs.
Are you real or is this another illusion?
I don't know what's next for us, but I know thisit's going to be better than Oblivion. I wish Gilraen would stop worrying.

Kind of these Star-Gazers to let us set up shop here in their observatory. I guess it makes them feel safer. I still feel like a kagouti in a glass-blower's shop, though.nnBut what brings you all the way up here? Looking to join the Fighters Guild?

You certainly have interesting friends. nnI can't say I like sticking my neck out, but you did save me from those bandits. So if you need help finding this Reinhold's Retreat Hara mentioned, I'll do my best.

Reinhold's Retreat. Is that truly what she said? I thought my ears had conspired to fill my mind with the foulest lies, but if you heard the same .nnPerhaps I was meant to be here for reasons other than just stopping Tarish-Zi.
I don't care what you have. <<1>> doesn't leave the stocks unless Magistrate <<2>> tells me himself.
Careful not to get caught.

I can't thank you enough. You trusted me, even when I'd failed to show the same trust in you.nnI won't make that mistake again. From here forward, we must work together closely if we're to defeat the Serpent.
Thank you for returning our aspects to us. We have discussed among ourselves and concluded that the Lost One is too powerful for us to defeat.nnThe best we can hope for is to weaken her.
The Lost One is no longer in control of her actions. Now is the time to strike.
Onsi's blade, this one will be easy.
I'll meet you at Cosh Hall. I'll be talking to people, seeing what I can find out.
Ooh, this is going to be so much fun! I'll see you there, don't be late!
I'll meet you there. Find me inside, I'm going to be trying not to be accosted by idiots.
Lerien is lucky to have found you. That lazy thief.
Many thanks for ridding this place of those ghastly zombies and such. Now my research can begin in earnest!
Blessings of Morwha be upon you, friend. Water is more than simple drink to my people, so my gratitude is two-fold. nnPlease look over my goods. I hope you can find something you need.
Thanks for the help. Sali'ma said everything is fine now, but I'm still not going anywhere near that water. Nothing but wine and juice for me from now on.
These dung-headed Daedra worshippers conspired to steal from Sali'ma. The Dark Elf ran into the ruins. This dead one drew a dagger and hesitated.nnMalihaz is a son of Alkosh. He does not hesitate.
I just have a few things I want to tie up here before heading out.
Some of our fellows have been trickling indisoriented and afraid. My brother has not been among them. I ask for your prayers. I don't know what I'd do without him.
If you have the coin to purchase my wares, I will be surprised. Buy something, if you can.
Good luck with your draughts! Don't do anything I wouldn't do!
Who  who sent you? No, no. Don't tell me. Just say what you need and go.
Hello there! What can I get you, a brew or a story? My brews are strong and my stories are long!
What are you gawking at? We're just  taking notes. Off with you!
Here we are, Garion's Hope. Looks like a Nord mining town, but don't be fooled.nnWe're going to need to get in, the listening post is probably hidden around here somewhere.
I have art to make. What do you want?
I spend hours every day hunched over my anvil. Good to stretch my muscles for a moment. What can I get you?

Split-Nose and this one are old acquaintances.nnThat one has troubles of the mind, and has requested this one help him make sense of his mind and self.nnAside from the hoarding, it seems to be going well.
You must be new here. Are you insane? This place is a dump and you're an idiot for coming here.nnAnd you'd be a fool as well, being on the streets here without one of my weapons at your side.
Do as the aspects asked. And hurry. The Serpent gets closer to his goal with every passing moment.
People who need storage solutions come to me. That is the way of things here in Abah's Landing.nnSuch things do not change, and there are many such things here.
You're new around here, yeah? We don't tend to get too many new people in Abah's Landing.nnWonder what you're here for. Anything requiring the finest of tailored leatherwear?
Walker, let Mamaea caress you with the finest of her silks and cloths, yes?nnFor none knows how to best suit a body like yours  but Mamaea and her tailoring.
Good luck.
The sun is out!
Remember to think of Sharesh should you find yourself with spare coins.
Hello, darling. Anything you'd like to stow in our vaults? Or perhaps we have something of yours, hmm?nnWe do so try to be  accomodating to our clientele.
My time is very important, so please don't waste it.nnI have much to do to ensure everything within my vault is still there. Because  that's where I like it.
If you're not here for alchemical supplies, you need to leave. You could be a thief!nnI don't tolerate thieves, they drive me to drink. But, if you're a customer  By all means, stay.
You have done for us what we could not do for ourselves. We will remember this.
The Scaled One is gathering our other aspects. We cannot hope to overwhelm him, but we must hope to match him. Our best chance is to face him on an even footing.
nyi - on return wine step
It is I, Taminal, to whom you speak. nnAnd I,Taminal, am the only purveyor of tailoring supply on this miserable rock. Do you have such needs?
Unfortunately, I have to ply my trade for the halfwits on this island and sell my wares to people like you.nnMy condition is expensive to maintain. It's necessary.
You are new here, I take it? I am bad with faces, apologies if I have asked this already.nnLet me know if you have need of me!
Anything I can get for you, dear? I have a wholesome assortment of stock for the discerning chef.nnOf course, if you don't need anything, that's fine too. I enjoy company.
We've done it!
This town needs an arena. My business demands bloodshed, and having some sport on which to bet is always delightful.nnThe magistrate is a fool for not building one.
Hey, you. You looking for magic items? Staves, trinkets, enchanted jewellery nnI can supply you. If you're in the market, that is.
We're through here, mortal. Your presence is no longer required. It would behoove you to leave, in fact.
Excellent work! I do hope you didn't damage the merchandise too much.
Come to buy from me? Good. When Cosh loops me into his inner circle, I'll remember my best customers.nnAfter all, I keep meticulous records.
Like I said, just look for rounded stones with a reddish rust color tint to them and you are in business.
This doesn't look like the Aetherian Archive. It's going to be hard being the first to the top if you start in the wrong place.nnHa! I slay me.
On to the next thing, shall we?

"by Zeg gra-Dushnn"Orc forge-wives are full of themselves. They say they're the only ones who know how to smith. I say you should read my book, learn the basics of blacksmithing, and show those stuck-up forge-wives what they're really full of."
You're a damned good crewmate. You ready to see this thing through?
<<1>> should be at the Lass. If you don't find her inside, head upstairs and out to the balcony. She always prefers the feel of a good ocean breeze.
Hail, soldier. Glad to see another comrade in arms. Short on supplies? I've got plenty to sell. Take a look.
Hara's deception was a clever one, even if it only stalled the Serpent for a time. We were all fooled. nnI can't be angry. This means we actually stand a chance.
Hurry. We'll be leaving shortly after you. Just a couple small preparations and we'll be all set.
I haven't had a moment's peace around here since Nicolas stormed off. Gwennether insists on being my "assistant," even though I never asked for her help.
I assumed Vexa needed some help, so I volunteered my time.

When the High Elves approach you, remember that I warned you. Those women have a strange way of spotting anything related to the Star-Gazers.nnAnd guess what? If you're working with Hara, you're related to us now.

I no longer feel the Learned One's presence. Has she finally decided to leave us?nnI suppose it was time. I never believed she would stay indefinitely. And with the Great Source gone, perhaps it's time the Firstmages returned to Tamriel.
That mere mortals could best the Mage so easily gives me pauseI question whether that kind of power belongs in mortal hands. But I thank you for your help.

Have you seen the High Elves that were here by any chance?nnI was supposed to keep an eye on them, and I only turned away for a moment and now they're gone! Oh, Hara is going to be very angry with me.
<Without the blackened gem, the orrery holds no further interest.>
You  you've been to the upper floors, haven't you?nnWhat did you do? I no longer feel the presence of the Learned One.
Have you talked with Nick and Vexa? It's your choice who you want to join you for this operation, rook. You don't have to choose me just because I'm the leader.
We've got everything we need to rescue Gwen. I'm glad you've got our backs here.
I saw you enter the upper floors. And I no longer feel the presence of the Learned One. What exactly did you do?nnI told you not to go up there! You've irked her and she's left us, hasn't she?
Sorry to unload all that onto you, rook. Sometimes I just need to let it all out.
Can you believe it? Hara is the Celestial Thief. She's been among us all this time. It's just like the stories from my childhood!
All this time, the Thief was right here. I always thought there was something odd about Hara. She knew so much for one so young.nnStill, never in a thousand years would I have guessed it.
How can I help a fellow Star-Gazer?
So Hara is the Thief and the Thief is Hara. Now I really do need a drink.
You survived a raid into the Citadel? Tell this Khajiit, have you ever considered an exciting career as caravan guard?
The Tribunal protect you for clearing the mountain path.nnI didn't think you had the heroic look about you, but clearly I was wrong.

And so you return! None have done so beforeI assume you defeated whatever menace awaited within!nnThat you return without any of my fellow Redguard pains me. Don't tell me of their fateI will go and discover for myself.
So you're the newest recruit? And you are?
You don't look like much to start, but Danni knows how to pick 'em. Tell me, what do you call yourself?
So you're going on a little rescue operation, eh? That sounds like fun. Who're you going to choose to join you?
Did you talk to Danni about the operation? You know you have to choose someone to join you, right?
Whenever you're ready.
I see you return, friend! Do you return victorious?nnHave you made it to the top of the Aetherian Archive?
You are trespassing on Aldmeri Dominion property. State your business.
We're here, on a secret island holding a covert government prison. Should be fun, right?
I don't feel comfortable about this mission, but we're here. Let's get started.
Xarxes Rebuke. I've heard stories about this place. Dark stories. This isn't a place a person coms voluntarily. But here we are.
Yes? State your business. I'm a very busy woman.
Let's get out of here.
Please, don't tell anyone I'm here. I'll come out, eventually. When it's quieter, and wealthy people aren't likely to threaten me.
Up and about, are we?
I'm sorry, friend. I'm afraid you cannot enter our challenges without a horse.nnDo not worryI'm sure the stablemasters in any city will be happy to sell you one.
Ha! I was worried you'd never wake up. You slept all the way from <<1>>. Right through the hurricane!
Greetings, mortal.
Hm. Talaya thinks you completed this course too easily. She will have to try harder next time.nnPerhaps more  werewolves.
You completed the challenge? Unbelievable. It seems everyone will win a race before Thrauar.
Ah! Don't frighten an old man like that!
Back on your feet already? You needn't offer me gold, I only did what anyone should. I helped someone in need.nnUnlike some people I could point at .
Quickly! Before the guards spot you!
Always good to see you, my friend. You are like a cousin to me, truly.
My new friend. I am glad to speak with you again. I have much I wish to discuss.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
What? You beat my course? Hm. Well, maybe this one can finally leave this burning wasteland.
I see you've returned. Good for you. One of these days, my luck will change.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
Ah, so you made it? Talaya is relieved. Just in case Ahmat succeeds in convincing the queen to try the course, this one wanted to make sure it was not too dangerous.
You are an impressive rider. I admit it. We should race sometime  after I get a new horse.
My friend. I am Ahmat of the Black Horse Couriers. My assistant Talaya and I have prepared a riding challengea winding course across dangerous terrainand a prize for the fastest rider.
How did you do it? Talaya believed she had designed a course that would be impossible to complete.nnApparently, she was wrong.
Don't come complaining to me. You may be stuck in Coldharbour, but at least you have a horse. Some of us are not so lucky!
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.

Sleek ride! You have impressed Talaya, and that is not always easy. nnShe slaved away on this course for weeks, trying to make it perfect for these brutish Nords, but they said it was impossible to complete in time. You proved them wrong, yes?
You finished the course already? No fair! Give me a horse and I will finish it in half the time! I'll show you all what riding a horse in Eastmarch is all about!

You completed the course? Wait a minute! What horse were you riding? You'd better not have bought it from some shady little Bosmer!nnThat little bastard stole my horse. I'll find him if it's the last thing I do!
Hold on. This can't be right. Talaya tested this course! No one could have finished it so fast as you have.nnTell the truthyou cut corners, didn't you?
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.

You completed the course. So what? Anyone could make this run. Talaya made it too easy for all these milk-drinkers. nnMaybe Ahmat should let me design the courses. Yes. I think i'll discuss this with him soon.

Talaya wonders if this is really a good place for a riding course. The Bosmer only like to run around in the foresta and play games.nnThis one is very glad you ran the course. Otherwise, her work would be wasted. So you finished fast, yes?
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
Wait a minute! You finished the course? Already? Did the Wood Orcs just wave you right through?nnTalaya has a hard time believing you beat the course so easily. Are you sure you didn't cheat?

I did it. I can't believe it, but I did it. I stole one of the Wood Orcs' mammoths! Ahmat and Talaya are going to eat their words when I finish the course riding this .nnNow I just need to figure out how to get a saddle on it.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.

No  no! This cannot be! You cannot have completed this course so quickly, so easily! nnTalaya spent weeks designing this. She was convinced that it would be years before someone would do this! How did you do it?
You finished the course, eh? You must be a good rider  not as good as me though. I will prove it too. Soon. nnYes. That Baandari trader should be here any minute with my new horse.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.

You finished the course? Already? Bah! Talaya is finished with these Ebonheart Pact lands. The people and the horses are just too tough for this one to design a course that really challenges!nnWas it really so easy for you?
So you finished the course? nnIt's not fair. I don't like you any more.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
What? You completed the course? This was Talaya's most devious challenge yet!
You completed the course? The Khajiit will not be happy to hear it. I heard her boasting that this course is unbeatable.
Are you sure you didn't cheat? Maybe you asked the mages of Shad Astula for a teleportation spell, hm?
You are a skilled rider. Maybe you can teach old Thrauar a thing or two. I keep getting attacked by kwama or angry Ashlanders.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
Oof. Talaya thinks she overdid it this time. Too many bloodfiends.
In truth, I haven't attempted this race yet. My horse is a little skittish. That's all.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
How did you complete the course so fast? This one got lost no less than 22 times while constructing it!
It's this damn marsh. Everything looks the same. And the horse is spooked by crocodiles.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
Ugh, my poor ribs. You may think this course easy, but the mountains are not friendly to Khajiit claws.
Every time I think I should give up, I remember dear Mother. "Thrauar, my boy, you are a Nord. You might not be the strongest or the brightest, but no one can take that away from you."
What is it? Is this about the fish? I took what I paid for!nnUm, never mind. What do you want?
