What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
This one likes this course the best. It is the route she took with her father when he was first teaching her to skulk in the shadows.
I think the Khajiit has used some kind of spell to keep me from winning.
<This Dominion marine is dead.>
Good to see you again. Nice work with Banu.
Go talk to Vexa, let's get out of here. I'll see you back at the Barrows.
This is a day unlike many. The Shadows have blessed us this day.nnI'm feeling a little faint, even. Incredible!
I'll meet you back at the Barrows. I'm going to finish my drink.
That pot above me, that's where the tokens are. Look past my shoulder, up on the balcony.nnThat's what you'll need. I'm going to see about slipping inside a different way.
See if you can't get one of the tokens. I'll see if I can't get a disguise and meet you inside. I have a few ideas on how to pull this off, thanks to Danni.
I can't believe the dream is coming true!
Again, I wouldn't let word of what you did to our little Danni get around. Honor amongst thieves and all. Probably a rule you need to know more about.
Least I don't have to up security around here.
I hope Nicolas still has some big plans to continue the guild's worth.
I'm in the middle of a ritual.
Go on. What are you waiting for? You've already got the open invitation.
Welcome, mortal.
Ah, you've returned! I trust that my perfidious acolytes have been properly dealt with?
Go. You are needed at the Fort. The Moons have spoken and will not tell you again.
We leave for Daggerfall. Coming or not?
The Summerset Isles call me back. We're leaving for Vulkhel Guard soon if you need transport.
Though I hate to leave her, work calls back in Davon's Watch. If you need a ride, we're leaving soon.
Hjargredda just returned, but she was too shaken up to say very much. What did you find?
Hello there.
Little busy here.

Atildel says you're here to help. This one hopes you know what you agreed to. There's some kind of spirit lurking within these cavernsthe Gazers call it a "Celestial Serpent"it will wreak havoc if it ever escapes.nnYou cannot let that happen!
Captain Whitemane is hold up in Privateer's Pier. See to it that the grave reclaims the cove.
Atildel says you're actually going in there. Do you have a death wish?nnThe Celestial Serpent himself leads the Scaled Court in these caverns!

Atildel said you were planning to enter these caves. I can't believe she convinced you. We've been trying to get her to leave.nnThe Celestial Serpent stalks this place. He has plans for Craglornfor all of Tamriel.
I demand to be set free!nnYou ingrates think this attack on Sanctum Ophidia will go unanswered? The master will digest all of you! Slowly!
Has the little goat finished its work?
I'm sure he just wants to praise you for a job well done.
Well done. Very well done.
Oosh should be just outside my chambers.
Ah, it's good to see you again.
I wish I could do it myself. I'd love to see the life in her eyes drain away and know I was the one responsible.
I admit, I feel wretched in doing this. I had hoped the threat on my life would be over.
Hope you enjoy your stay while you're here.
It's probably about time I got home to get supper ready.
I think I hear a mug of ale calling my name.
I noticed a few clouds in the sky. I hope it doesn't mean rain.
Nice thing about beggin' in the Dale, the people aren't stingy here.
That blasted cat. If she runs off one more time, I'm calling it quits.
Thank the gods this day is almost over.
I love the smell of fish roasting over an open flame. Can't wait to cook up some supper.
What'll it be? You look like you could use a drink.
How exciting was that? Right?
It feels good to be out of that cell. Thanks, mate. Though, really, you didn't have to do that.
You go on ahead. I'm going to stay here to see if I can learn anymore about the Dominion's plan for Shadowfen. Thank you for keeping the keystone out of their hands.
Dominion soldiers here? Have you come to free me or kill me? Whichever it is, do it quickly!
Thank you, thank you so much! You won't regret this, master assassin. I swear!
Be not afraid, my loyal protector. I'm fine. I just  wait.nnYou! It's you!
I heard Marganus' screams. You killed him, then.
You spared the worm, I see.

Atildel says you're willing to head into those cavesface the Serpent. You've certainly got gumption. Might change your mind if you saw what it did to us.nnYou're going to need equipment either way. What do you say? Give me your money.

Did I hear the High Elf correctly? You're going into those caverns?nnWe're in no shape to do it, so you might as well. But you'll need some potent soul gems to take those cultists on. Lucky for you, I have a few lying around.
So you're the one that these two miscreants found, are you?
You're back. How did events play out?
Go, and be careful. They are two of our most skilled assassins.
Better hurry.
Good luck.
I better get back to work.
I just  I just need some time alone. But thank you for helping us.
Banu will pay for this!
That Banu!
Yes, yes. I am the Duchess Sahmanza. You have caught me in a frivolous mood. What can I do for you?
Welcome to my lounge, new friend! What can the Duke of Tigonus do for you?
In the name of His Royal Highness, as representative of his name, I greet you. What may I do for you?
I would avoid mingling there if I were you. Getting close to people at a funeral to add yet another death to their toll can't be good for the mind. And yours needs to be clear.
Stendarr defend me!
Thank Jone and Jode. This one thought today would never come.nnHe will tell his children about you.
Another Dark Brother? You're not expected here.

By the Eight, you're alive! You've been gone so long. I was beginning to think I should have tried harder to keep you out of the ruins.nnBut tell me, was what I feared true? Was the Scaled Court harvesting more nirncrux?
My dear friend, I must apologize profusely for our rude treatment of your most delicate person. Please understand that no offense was intended.
Speak with my sister, Oosh. She will direct its first test.  When it has completed the test, it will meet me for its second test.
Good luck. You'll need it, my friend.
You're back? What did you find? No. Better you tell Scattered-Leaves first. He's been waiting for you to return.
Jarl Kalgar keeps himself pretty well protected.
I don't like that look on your face. It's bad, isn't it? No, I don't want to hear it. You should talk to Scattered-Leaves.
You're back, but where's Camaarie? Oh no, not Camaarie!
You look like you've seen a ghost. What's happening?
You have a determined stare. What have you seen?
You saw something awful out there, didn't you? Well, at least you made it back in one piece.
Now, I have a great task for you.
Ah, a commoner. Good to see that the Headman wants to mix things up. You'll fit in well.

You're back! Excellent! I was just about to look for someone to send in after you.nnBut tell us true, were you successful? Neither Veesk nor I would blame you for running away from that terrible monster.
Oh, hello dear! Welcome! You now stand among the most important people on the continent. We all gather for the signature season, the Reveltide of Tamriel!
Find those caches as quickly as you can. This goes on much longer, we'll be fighting the cult with nothing but bricks and foul language.
Oh, it's so good to see you! I'm glad you're here!
Our carts overflow with more wounded than tradegoods these days. And for what? More gold! nnThe price of prosperity is high. Too high, if you ask me.
I can feel the darkness within you, my child. Have you been ushered into Sithis's embrace?
I can see the mark of Sithis within its eyes. It is welcomed into the family.
Greetings.

And so the hero returns. I should have known you were the one to free us. Nerien'eth single-handedly trounced useven as the entire school stood ready to face him.nnBut if someone could defeat him it would be you.
Your choice is backed by my will. Speak to my new Listener, the one who will shoulder the burden anew.
Wrath. You have done much for the Brotherhood.nnThank you. I don't mean to be so formal. I'm still adjusting.
The Wrath speaks, a voice of merit above many.nnFrom the Night Mother to the Wrath, through the Listener, be honored: you have performed admirably.
Whenifyou succeed, I would speak with you before you leave. I'll wait by the docks.nnFear not. No Tenets shall be broken. After all, you honor Sithis with your deeds.
You know what they saywhen the Void gives you lemons, squeeze 'em into someone's eyes.nnOr is it "squeeze someone's eyes into 'em?" I think both could work, if you put your back into it.
"Whoosh." Elf capons.nnHeh.
Hope the mission went well. I heard screaming, but couldn't tell if it was out of sorrow or pain  or horror. Plenty of emotions at a funeral!
Have you seen Taara's "charnel gown?" A full suit of armor, complete with a closed helm! Leave it to soldiers to eschew funereal silks.
If you see Eamil embarrassing my family name, I give you leave to slap the smirk from his face.nnNo hestitation. Just a sharp smack.
Taara will soon be with her ancestors. Auri-El bless us all.
I hope Norion can forgive me.

I feared what it would take to defeat Nerien'ethfeared that he had grown in strength. He isn't the kind to remain idle. Not when he would slay his wife and destroy everything she held dear for power.nnAt least the day is won. You have my thanks.
Yes, yes, what is it? I don't have time for all thesennMy apologies. We're just  these are trying times. And doubly so for the Dragonstar Caravan Company. How can I help you?
I'm not holding out much hope of you finding any of my old squadmates, but please keep an eye out for them.
Here to swing a pick? Well, I'd think about another line of work if I were you. Mine's shut down. Closed until we sort out this whole Orc  snake  situation.
Garamiel says he's seen those damned gray-hides strip-mining just a few wheels from here. Some of kind of red ore. Makes me wonder what they're doing with it  and how much I could sell it for.
Been days since we've seen an ore wagon. Bah. A mineshaft's just a hole in the ground if you can't trade what you chip out of it.

Everyone's talking about "Serpent this" and "Scaled Court that." Honestly, how bad could it be?nnDo you know how many snakes I put an arrow through back in my acorn days? Maybe it's just time for me to go snake hunting again.

Did you hear about the six-legged, spear-tailed, goat-horned, monster? It was all they talked about around the cooking fire last night.nnEither red brittle has gotten into the water supply or people are a lot more gullible than I imagined.
Aetherian light take him! I was so certain I could best Nerien'eth this time. That I had strengthened my spells.nnIf you hadn't come back, we'd all be dead. Again.
I'm having visions of me in a crown  it's wonderful.

Skeetees grows weary of watering her roots here in town. These dry-skins do nothing but drink, fight, and sing like old frogs. I don't know what will evaporate firsttheir ale, their gold, or my patience.
Cowards! Boot-licking, snake-loving, rock-headed cowards .
Hey! You! Wanna hear a joke?
I'll be all right. You don't have to worry about leaving me alone here.nnGo on. Get to Dragonstar and help Cassi. And thanks again.
Not now!
It speaks. Why?
Iron Orcs? Pshaw! More like  like  paper Orcs! Gonna fold 'em up nice, write some bad words on 'em, and post 'em back to their ugly Orc mothers! Har!
I knew, in my heart of hearts, that I could count on you. Though we have known each other only a short time, we are patriots under the Covenant banner.
Look at him, fish! Trussed up like a little lamb, ready for the knife. Hah!
Some of those you rescued came through here, and I am told many others escaped the city.nnHave you rescued all that you can, for now, at least?
We found himwe found him, and we'll need help.nnHe slew so many of us.
Wait, I'm not your enemy. I need your help. If we work together, we can put an end to the Serpent's threat once and for all.nnShould I continue?
Can't believe we've got to reinforce the walls. Again. By Mauloch's mighty molars, I hate those Iron Orc bastards.
Yes, you caught this one. Again.
Here to swing a pick? If so I'd find another line of work. Mine's shut down till we sort out this whole Orc  snake  thing.
I sense that the darkness within the catacombs has subsided. Tell me, did you find the source of whatever disturbed the dead?
What're you lookin' at, chump? This camp's for Blood-Feathers only. Piss off.
Kelmen should have never confronted her alone. This Cassipia must pay for the blood spilled today!
Regent Cassipia reached for powers that were not hers to acquire.

I admit it. I didn't think our mission stood an Elf's chance in Orsinium of succeeding. But here we are!nnYour reputation is rightly deserved. And with any luck, those wards will hold for another thousand years.
Of course! It was right in front of me all this time!
Do you not want your reward? You've slain many Daedra to receive it.

Now yours is a face I haven't seen in a long time.nnDo you remember me? We met among the mountains of Skyrim. In Eastmarch, if I recall. We walked with giants. Put some brutish Orcs in their place. Good times!
This one has been informed that there are far fewer Daedra in the sewers than there were before. You have closed the portals to Coldhabour, yes?
Are you ready to be certified? I have time if you do.
Please. Hurry to Belkarth. I don't think you should keep the great warrior waiting any longer than is absolutely necessary.
It's good to see you again before the end, my friend. I was just saying one last farewell to my wife before I depart to find my final battle.
Find Skarath and retrieve War-sworn. That Iron Orc is not worthy to carry such a blade.nnTitus has earned my weapon a hundred times over. I would see War-sworn in his hands.
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
<No new commissions are available at this time.>
If you're ready to be certified, we should begin.
By the kindness of Jone and Jode!nnYou squashed that Daedroth! Reminds me of when I was youngbatting the other children around like balls of yarn!
No moreI beg you.nnWe should never have come. You can keep the woman. We'll tell Fingaenion we found nothing. I swear it!
<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"Certified Crafters, We Want Your Wares! Armor, Weapons, Bows, and Robes! Hone your craft and earn a reward!"
"CITIZENS of the DOMINION, MASTERS of the CRAFT await you in <<Z:1>>! New crafters shall be TRAINED! Accomplished crafters will be CERTIFIED! All at NO COST TO YOU!"
Help me.
You have my thanks. Without you, my husband would likely have been mauled by senches, let alone Daedra.nnOnly Dagon left to deal with, now.
Your timing is impeccable, my friend.nnI must've slaughtered a hundred of them. Never thought I would see the day, but I haven't the strength to swing my sword.

Fighting an endless sea of foes just isn't the same without a barrel of ale to wash it down. Let's hope Sovngarde is a bit more  hospitable.nnThis isn't Sovngarde, is it? I feel like I've been fighting for a week. Are there Daedra in Sovngarde?

I just slew three Daedra with the same laughing face.nnHogondar won't believe me, but I think it's the same one. How do you kill something that won't stay dead? Dammit it all! This place doesn't make any sense!
Give this one a moment, please. She just stopped a howling ball of flame with her face. Sobabe was excited to come here, but the Wood Elf was right.nnThis is the worst place in the world.
Please don't make me speak.
<Agonized groaning.>
Good to see another mortal step in. Not that we couldn't have handled that ourselves.
Seems like everyone had a pretty unpleasant experience. At least it wasn't Apocrypha.
I've given you my report. Now leave before you give away my position!
A glorious day, if Rabe-ma were to return! This one is grateful for all she has but still misses Rabe-ma.
Where in Oblivion ? Where did you get those?nnThose are official Imperial City records, property of the Magistrate's Office! They must have been misplaced. I demand that you turn them over at once.
Very good. Speak to Maj al-Ragath, and tell her to give you a bronze key. If you have the constitution, I will speak to you again when you are prepared to take a pledge.
While I pray you kill that creature, I don't hold out much hope. nnIf you do it, any memento you can bring me will be appreciated.
Glirion really is a good sort. Once you start taking pledges, you'll get used to him. We all do  eventually.

I'm going to send word to King Emeric. He may want us to make rescuing the Empress-Regent our top priority. nnOnce we find a way into the tower, I hope you're still around. I'd like you to be the one we send in there.

See if you can find that Dremora bastard. He was here in the Market Sewers when I met him. Fought right over there. Probably left a stein's worth of blood on those stones. Ugh.nnOh, I should tell you he had some friends too.
I am glad to see you survived the sewers. Many others have not been so lucky.nnTell me, though, did you find my clan brother?
Be wary. Those sewers are full of Leovic's beloved Daedra. Hrmph. The fool.
Thank you ever so much. I just can't seem to do these things on my own any more. Old eyes and older bones, ay?

You destroyed the wraith. Not many can say that, friend. You have done his victims, and me a great service. They're free, for now.nnUnfortunately, he will be back. He never truly dies. More's the pity, eh?

My greatest desire would be to bring my companions' bodies back, to be buried among their ancestors. But I saw the bodies dragged away by those Daedra. I can't even imagine what will become of them. nnMy knife will have to do.

Oh  you've made it? My friend. nnThe children are ready for supper, and my time is almost done. Do you see how strong they are? I will give them a strong start. They will do great things. Won't you, my loves?
I have some theories about this composite, but I'll need alchemical tools to test them. Perhaps in Orsinium .
That centurion core is just what we needed. Thank you again for your help.
No time to talk now. I have to start thinking about the final assault. I tell youwhen we take the main keep, that's going to be a glorious moment!
<This tome is bitingly cold to the touch, and lies open to a page that reads, "For those mortals wishing to make a Pactspeak the words, in your own frail tongue, 'come slow and bring four keys.'">

Now I just have to wait for our scouts to return from the coast. As soon as they arrive though, I am leaving this gods-forsaken place and going back to Hammerfell.nnI think it will take at least a week's leave at the shore to thaw out my bones!
Well? Did you test the whistle?

It took months to arrange this deal! Everyone was going to profit! nnThe Orcs get new ballistae and this one and her partners were going to get a pile of gold! This is what comes from trusting that mangy Breton smuggler!
A disaster. An unmitigated disaster.
Welcome! Prepare to be transported through time! Look into the past to see the future! Behold, the deeds of the Orcish people!

Rumor has it that there's an old royal tomb not far from the city. They say the first Orc KingTorog gro-Igronis buried out there. nnIf someone were looking for treasure, that might be a good place to look. I'm not interested, of course .
I'm ready. Do you have the ingredients?
Excuse me. Have you seen a Nord named Snordan?
Ho there, buy you  I mean buy you  I mean buy me a drink?
If you've never tried one, you really should go see Nednor and get yourself a frozen egg. Wrap it in some warm bread. Mmm. It's my favorite thing.
I don't care what Elvira says. I'm not leaving without the Posset. nnEventually the riekr will go back into their caves, and then I can get my ship back!
I shudder to think that such a priceless find would be destroyed as part of some ritual, albeit I suppose it is no longer my concern.
Mazgroth? Is that you?
This door will soon freeze over, but it's for the best. The Orcs in there could hardly be called Orcs anymore, could they?
Oh, hello. I'm Orluguk. The chief's daughter. If you have business here, you shoud talk to my mother.
You know  I could always set up an exclusive contract with the Mages Guild. If the potions were sold though the guild, I bet the guard couldn't do anything about it.
Speaks-with-Feathers sure is a strange bird. nnYou know I tried one of those frozen eggs myself one time? All I got was a chipped tooth!
He spent all that money to get himself a durzog and now he doesn't even want it? I'll never understand Elves.

Tell Azaro we're coming just as fast as we can. We may not have everything we promised, but we've still got what they need to build the ballistae. nnIf you get there in time to save the deal, I'll give you a cut off our end.
It's like a nightmare  what they're doing down there. I managed to sneak away  but someone has to stop them .
After that antidote you made me and a warm mug of Dark Jamocha, I believe I am on the path to recovery. nnIf you were not able to recover the schematics, I will simply have to try to remake them.
Thank you! This one kept hoping they would get bored of the torture sessions. They never did.nnThese people must be stopped. They're planning an attack that'll overrun Shadowfen above.
Hurry up and put the note in the pot, please. It's a strange jar our father picked up while adventuring in Skyrim. You can't miss it.
This is just fascinating!
Malacath's tusks. Leave me alone!
It is hard to know how to talk to Grookh when he gets like this. What is there to say? No words will bring his clan back to him.
Thank you for explaining matters to the chieftain. I'll see that these automata are put to good use in Orsinium.

Easy enough. You'll find Grand Forge-Mother Alga at Scarp Keep in Orsinium. nnIf you need transport, I suppose I can cart you through Dragontail Pass, but you'll be on your own from that point. Just let me know when you're ready to go.

So Gurgum finally found you? Took his damn time  but you're here. That's what counts. nnWelcome to Orsinium. Amazing how fast we've rebuilt, isn't it? Be proud, young one, it's your home too. We Orsimer are unstoppable when we work together.

I don't want to take any more of your time. I have duties to attend to at Orsim Temple, and I know the king awaits you at Frostbreak Fort.nnI will ask Trinimac to bless you both in achieving triumph over those dreadful Reachmen.

Thank the Eight! You have to help me! These foul little riekr are planning to eat me or something. nnThey stripped me of all my belongings, my clothes too, the little bastards. Even if they don't eat me, I'm going to freeze to death!

See you back at the keep then. Hopefully you'll get a chance to try some of Hearth-wife Bumzal's Mountain Bear Hash. It's the best you'll find anywhere.nnYes. We'll have a feast. After you show the Ice Heart to the clan chiefs, of course.
Shawaz said you saved his life. Did you find the ballista plans?
I'm not the only one who doesn't want those machines working in Orsinium. This isn't Malacath's way.
What? Who are you?
If you find any of my old squadmates, tell them Martina was thinking of them.
If you find any of my old squadmates, tell them I was thinking of them.
An empty crate sits here, waiting for a supply drop.
Oh! Hey there. You startled me.
Whoa! Who the blazes are you and what are you doing here?
Yo, I'm the Red Coach. You should join Red Team. We really know what we're doing. So, join up?
Hi. O, I'm supposed to tell you. I represent blue team. We're number 0. Join?
It's not fair! We had them! We were almost through! The damn birds! I hate them! Hate them! Hate them!nnLook at them! Now they're just sitting out there, picking at the bones of my warriors!
Shh! Try not to alert the Winterborn down there. We're preparing an ambush, and I don't want it spoiled.
Don't worry. Everything is going exactly according to plan here. Exactly. We are slowly pushing our way up the hill. nnWe'll recapture the gate in no time at all. No time at all I tell you!
My scouts ambushed a party of Dremora who were close to discovering our location. Tell me you've made progress in shutting down the portals to Coldharbour.
The report for the Pact is your concern now. Do not fail in delivering it.
I hear there are far fewer Daedra in the sewers than there were before. I trust that we have you to thank for this?
I've given you my report. Now leave before you give away my position!
I can't believe you did it! Old Logronakh sure has an eye for talent, eh Chief?
Oh my  poor Mazhun.
Interesting times lie ahead. An outsider chieftain will spark sharp words and swords that cut into the rifts of Orsinium. Be prepared.
<It's apparent that he suffered horribly before he was killed.>

Such cruelty  this mindless slaughter  I can't get the images out of my head. Why? I can't understand.nnMalacath. He won't tolerate such trespass! He can't. They must drown in blood for what they've done!
I think I'll go home to the Alik'r Desert after this. Get as far away from Nellic Sterone as I possibly can.
Find Captain Thorasa as soon as you can. The general isn't the most patient person.
Kharza says you got our quarry back. I guess I was wrong about you, outsider.
I tell you the truth, I was half-tempted to just bonk Lothangar on the head and drag him all the way back to Orsinium. nnIf you can convince him to come willingly, however, that would be much easier.

I'm just going to stay here and savor the moment. I've looked forward to it for a long time.nnIf you come to Orsinium, come see me. I'll probably be staying in the guest's suite in the palace or something.
Yes, you killed a couple of fool Daedra. Must all peasants be congratulated for doing their work?nnWe have the Ruby Throne, but the Elder Scroll is still out there.

The Bloody Curse has exacted its price from the heathens. You served well as the instrument of my vengeance, mortal. nnYou are strong, an exemplar of what it means to be an Orc, to be one of my people.

Thanks, friend. I can't tell you how much this means. My brother's probably been searching for meyou know how big brothers are.nnHe'll take it hard, but he needs to just leave. It would break our mother's heart if neither of us survived.
All this fuss over a hammer. Old ideas, old traditions, where have they gotten us?

Go on in the throne room. The king may not be in there right now, but he should be there soon. nnHe said you can go ahead and present the Ice Heart to the chiefs whenever you think the moment is right.
Here I was  looking forward to this voyage for so long, looking forward to joining my people in Wrothgar .nnNow I just want to go home to Stormhaven.
Moj-Argo is confused. All he can see is white. Where is the city? Where are the Orcs?nnPerhaps this one should have stayed on the boat.
I can't believe it. Not only did I leave all my clothes behind on the ship, but I left my comb too!nnI might just have to go back.
I don't give a guar's arse whether these logs came from Valenwood or not. When it's this cold, the Green Pact doesn't apply.

I wish I could muster more enthusiasm for your offer of help. I've just seen so much. I can't believe anything can get better. nnI hope, if you truly return to me, that the monster will be dead and my only memento of the past returned.

I wish I could muster more enthusiasm for your offer of help. I've just seen so much. I can't believe anything can get better. nnI hope, if you truly return to me, that the monster will be dead and my only memento of the past returned.

I wish I could muster more enthusiasm for your offer of help. I've just seen so much. I can't believe anything can get better. nnI hope, if you truly return to me, that the monster will be dead and my only memento of the past returned.
Treasonous bastards! How dare they walk out on me like that?nnLook  I need you more than ever now, but I'm just not in the mood to talk at the moment. I-I hope you understand.

The chiefs will have heard about your role in killing the Ice Heart. Hopefully, that means they'll be respectful. nnIf they give you trouble though, tread carefully. The last thing we need is more bad blood between us and them.
You're not flirting with my wife, are you?

I hope you can forgive my anger. I certainly have no issue with you. On the contrary, I owe you my life.nnIt's simply that  watching so many of my fellow priests get cut down  I fear I have not taken this seriously enough.
Hello.
Hello.
Hello.
I have other tasks to do for Bazrag, but perhaps I will see you back at the Clanhold.
<This dunmer alchemist seems to have perished during the raid.>
Winter on the range. It's almost poetic. The stillness. The quiet. The cold fit to freeze your  fingers off.
Please hurry, if you can. Semusa-la cannot face General Nedras unless he has heard from Captain Thorasa.
She appears to have gotten away, but I am free thanks to you.nnWhat of Kurog, did he send you to help?
This is the dawn of a new age for Orcs. I now have the leverage to return Orsinium to its ancient glory. And perhaps my rise will encourage other women to follow in my stead.
Completed Gloorig.
Hunt tutorial.

White-Gold Tower belongs to the Empire again, but there's much work left to do. Where has the true Clivia gone? I have to speak to the Imperial generals. They'll be  pleased to know a Daedra has been leading them.nnSo many questions left to ask.
The now full crate sits here, waiting for you to sign the shipment manifest.
Testing
You look like you want to get paid for something. Well, spit it out.
We never seem to run out of Daedra to kill down here. We're just lucky that way.nnWho'd you take care of?
Well, did you earn your pay today?
<The Hunting Board has no notices posted.>
Ah, the smell of steam and ash. A strange combination, to be sure, but in this context, I might say it was the scent of victory.nnWere you able to extinguish any of the fires?

What are you doing in here? This place is for the weak and the wounded. nnYou look perfectly capable. That being the case, I wonderwhy aren't you outside trying to retake the temple from those accursed Daedra?
I can't wait to get back into the arena now. The Daedra will be expecting me to fall, but they'll be in for a surprise.
The funny thing is that I've been holding back, fighting defensively because I knew I didn't have any way to heal.nnNext bout, the Daedra are going to see the true extent of my abilities.
Look at you, Walker, still stalking the streets unscathed. Your step seems a bit heavier though. Are you weighed down with treasures for Aishah?
I'm not going anywhere.nnThis isn't going to work twice.
I can't find it. I've looked everywhere, and I can't find it anymore.nnIt has to be here!

There you are! I heard the most wonderful scream of agony that really sounded like it was coming from that infernal Scarhea. To hear it suffer was beautiful.nnDoes that mean you killed it? Please say yes.
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU ARE NOT IN THE MAW OF LORKHAJ, NOR ARE YOU ON THE QUEST
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
Shining-Eyes stopped in a little while ago. He actually erected the spine of gratitude for sending the shirt. nnThey grow to maturity so fast. I remember when he was just a little spotted egg.

Kaoc! This shirt feels like fresh, warm mud. I am embarrassed that my mother asked you to perform such a petty errand, especially because it was my own fault.nnAll the same, I erect the spine of gratitude.
Remember. You have to remain stealthy for the spell's effects to be active. nnBanish a few of the Veilweavers and then return to let me know if it worked.
Two of my babies are back! Please hurry and find the last one.
I believe that each flesh colossus has several of the sacs I need. Necrotic hoarvor have only one apiece.nnWhichever is easiest for you to find and slay
target: it makes no difference to me. The sacs are basically the same. Good luck.

source: Are you insane? Don't stop to chat with me, get up there!
<The crate contains ample space for deliveries, and a sheaf of manifest papers.>
Don't bother looking for my scouts. Just blow the horn. They'll find you.
As Azaro said, it is good that all was not lost when the ship wrecked, but everything depends on whether they can make it Orsinium in time.nnThey are on their way, though, yes?
If you see my father, tell him I'm safe. I'll leave for the Arboretum refuge as soon as I can.
Ah, you've returned.
The truth is a bitter pill to swallow. Now go. I don't want to speak about this any more.
Please hurry. Aklash will have my head if she doesn't get that report soon.
You've got to help!
You've got to help!
<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"Certified Crafters, We Want Your Wares! Potions, Glyphs, Food, and Drink! Hone your craft and earn a reward!"
You've got to do something! Without your help we're all doomed.
White-Gold Tower has been home to the Empire since the early First Era. To see Daedra make a mockery of it atop the Ruby Throne burns my soul.
Sister Arminus was right about one thing: you know how to kill Daedra.
Watch your back. Only the Divines know how long these beasts have been lurking here. Empty rooms are never quite empty when Daedra are involved.
Please hurry to the Temple District. Every minute you delay, more souls are sacrificed to Molag Bal.
You did it! You're the arena champion. I didn't think you had it in you.
Save me from social progress!
Today would have been a dark one without you.nnDo me a favor and don't be so vocal about it, yes? You could cost me my job.
Continue your good work, soldier. By the Hist, this city will be ours.
The notes you found contain some fascinating information. Have you read them? I, for one, cannot wait to fell these anchors and claim the city for the Pact.nnAncestors guide you.

Look, this is going to take some time, but the more I think about it, the more I think that White-Gold Tower's going to wind up being our top priority. nnSo don't stray too far. Your skills will be in high demand again soon enough.

Tell Pudazi something, walker. You found the wizard's notes, so did you read them? nnThis one is thinking, it is a shame to risk such sweetmeat, but perhaps you are the best one to go and destroy these anchors.
Please tell me you closed those portals. I was just about to muster a few of these slack-jawed cubs. I'll tell you trueI don't like their chances.
You did it! You're the winner! I knew you had it in you!
Greetings.
The Rat heard the announcements for arena fights, and he thought he heard the name "Anthas." nnDoes that mean you were able to deliver the poultices?
This one has heard tales of an Arena champion! How delightful. I must confess, I am surprised they let you leave. These Daedra are strange creatures, eh?

Did the Bosmer general send you? Nedras, or whatever his name is?nnI hope so. That cranky, little bastard didn't send enough soldiers. Between the Daedra and the other alliances, they're getting chopped down pretty quick.

Hey, do me a favor, will you? If you could  just keep this between us. This little rescue here. Not everyone likes my brother, you know?nnAnd I mean, really, it's just not relevant, is it? To other people, I mean. So yeah. Just quiet.

Even if the city is reclaimed, I suspect my term on the Elder Council has come to an end. nnI have a summer home south of the city. If it's still standing, I think I'll spend the remainder of my years down there.
Travel down the river is not cheap. It's a good thing your friend here is a fast talker.
Thank you. I had nearly given up hope. nnThe Daedra dragged me to the upper level of one of the houses here. Please, come quickly.
The lock on this Imperial coffer has been broken and all its contents have been removed.
I'd love to do business, but now isn't really a good time.
No salethe Guard is watching the docks. Come back later and we'll do business.
Not right now. Come back later, when the Guard scrutiny is less intense.
I understand your frustration, but I have too much inventory at the moment.
Sorry, I can't help you right now. Return later and we can work something out.
How good to see you! Unfortunately, now isn't a good time. Come back later when I've moved my stock.
Sometimes the heat is too much, even for me. Perhaps another time.
No, we are closed. And this one's head aches. Come back later. Much later  ulp.
If you'd been here earlier, I'd have given you my full attention. Come back and see me later.
Hmm. I'm at capacity. Come back later.
Oh dear, it seems I've outspent my means! Come back later, will you?
Not right now. The Guard is on to me!
I'd try to help out, but I have my hands full right now. Come back later.
Sorry. Not buying anything until I move what I've got.
Turns out you can have too much of a good thing. Come back later, hmm?
Make yourself scarce. I can't move anything else right now.
Hm. I'm only allowed do business with Enforcers. Talk to Osgug if you want to join.
I'm so sorry, but I only deal in Enforcer business. You should talk to Osgug.
I do business with Enforcers only. Talk to Osgug if you must bother someone about membership.
Oh, I wish I could help you, but this is Enforcer business. Talk to Osgug. He'll get you sorted!
I only deal with Enforcers. Tedious, I know, but those are the rules. Talk to Osgug, if you must.
You should join the Enforcers. It would be an absolute pleasure to do business with you. Talk to Osgug.
Not an Enforcer? Can't help you.nnDon't ask about membership. Bother Osgug instead.
We only serve Enforcers. We should serve drinks. What was I saying?nnOh yeah, talk to Osgug. He can get you a drink. I mean, he can get you into the Enforcers.
I can't let non-Enforcers in on Enforcer business. Talk to Osgug if you want to join.
Sorry, Enforcers only. Want to buy or sell? Talk to Osgug.
Forgive me, but I only deal in Enforcer business. Talk to Osgug to join.
You want to deal? Become an Enforcer  then we can talk. Osgug will show you what to do.
Oh, I'd love to help you, but you must be an Enforcer first. Talk to Osgug about joining!
Oh dear, this is awkward. You aren't an Enforcer, so I can't do business. You should talk to Osgug.
You want to do business with the Enforcers? Become one. Talk to Osgug.
Enforcer business only. Come back once you've spoken to Osgug.
Go on. Don't worry about me. This is what I want.
I'm sorry to see that you've turned to the life of an outlaw. I'd implore you to change your ways. Nothing good comes of preying on the weak and helpless.

Be wary, vestige. Our very plane of existence is in peril. The threat of Molag Bal looms across all Tamriel, and chaos spreads in its shadow. nnDanger roams the land and will assume many forms. Do not let it catch you off-guard.
Any luck with recruitment so far?
I appreciate everything you did for Julien and me. When he returns from his tour of duty, we're going to get married!
Greetings friend.  I haven't forgotten what you've done for me.  Thank you again.
I'll call on <<1>> sometime soon. I just need to figure out what to say to her.
Not that I'm holding it against you or anything, but thanks for exposing me as a coward.  It's really helped my standing in town.
Welcome, friend. My land still lies fallow, but thank you for helping me find the cause.
Thank you so much for bringing Julien and I together.  I shall not forget it.
Have you found the hops I need? My flock grows impatient!
Why do we stand around wagging our jaws when there are Werewolves to be killed?
I can't believe you set a cat on my poor defenseless rats...
I can't believe he thought keeping rats in his house was a reasonable thing...
Quit messing in our affairs, lowling.
You are a kind, brave soul. I won't forget your help.
Don't worry. We'll put those swords you collected to good use.
What is it now?
I hear you've been quite useful in town.  Thank you for your help, the Divines know we need all we can get!
I am not here!
It's amazing how much faster one can work when one isn't being pestered, isn't it? Now shoo.
Well, you've fixed up all are drinkin' needs. I can't thank you enough. Oh wait, yes I can.
You're lollygagging when you should be killing wolves! Scoot!
Have you managed to find Simine and Dalomar? I fear the worst.
I appreciate you helping us out. We're extremely shortmanned here, and can use all the help you're willing to offer.
I will not forget what you've done for me, but I would rather not discuss it openly.
Refurbishing these will keep us busy.I'll let you know if we need any more.
That was... intense. Your steel helped greatly, friend.
Please, you must retrieve limbs for me. I can turn these maimed soldiers' lives around.
As soon as I discover the spy, I will let you know. For now, help the High Inquisitor.
What is it?
What's the latest?
I'm in the middle of a speech. Can this not wait?
I hear you stood up to Roche. Thanks for that.
I can understand why you would help Roche. Most people don't understand a man what lost his son.
So you got mixed up in the Dolban thing? That's a gamble I wouldn't have tried.
You did the right thing helping out Elsie. Thank you!
We will hold here. Hurry to Thrandor's Portal.
That was so scary!
Thetis... you found him.
Please, find my son! My business suffers without him!
Make haste! The brigands could be killing more dockworkers as we speak!
I see you found my old freind Arnand. I hope he's back up and running soon...
Thank you for rescuing my supplies from that ship... I wouldn't be able to cook Skooma without it...
What do you want to know?
The maptrap won't hurt the thief - it will simply immobilize them, that's all. I'm not a monster!
Did you convince Odette and the others to leave?
Bob said hi to me and I said hi back.
Are you mad?
Competence is a rare commodity. I look forward to seeing how you improve.
What have you and High Priest Canning discovered?
Are you ready to begin?
You seek a Bloodstone? We've none in Grayborne that I know of - but you come on the king's business, so I'll help however I can.
I see you have returned, in one piece, nonetheless! What news do you bring?
We must show these foolish Magis Order they cannot succeed.
I trust there were no problems?
Keep hunting! Remember, it may take some time to smoke out their leader.  Do not be discouraged.
I wish I could come with you. I want to be able to drive those wolves out myself.
I'm sorry, you'll have to excuse me. I'm very busy.
Have you made that delivery yet? Iamel is not a man who suffers waiting gladly...
Ah, it's the courier from Crosswych.  What may I do for you, friend?
Thanks for helping Elsie stay. She's a weird girl, but she's our weird girl.
Our tree will heal once the lake has been cleansed, but there is a more immediate threat.
Tell me you'll keep fighting with us! You're the best we've got!
My family! You've found my family!
You've made a better showing than us. Thank you. You have our respect.
Hurry! Tell Sergeant Bieller what happened here! Have him send a healer!
Do not worry for us. I will not allow my family to get separated again.
That was a close one!
I am not here!
Oh please hurry! My dress is already ruined, and I fear my complexion may be next!
You've saved the lives of many honest, hard-working men. I won't soon forget it, friend.
Did you need something?
Thanks for finding me that Drythistle!
Grit came home! He came home and he was okay!
What vitriol. I don't know how to calm them... can you do something about it?

William's probably run back home. nnThese scamps are dangerous, but I'm a farmer. I can run like the wind when I need to....nnPlease talk with William. He's too ashamed to actually face me, but if you tell him I forgive him, he might actually listen.
You've done it! Even now we sense the waning of Coldun's power within the Veil.
I am to aid you stranger. Together we shall drive the evil away or die trying!
Do not worry about Sly and the others! If anyone can stop this.. it will be him. Are you ready?
I do wonder how long you will survive.. Coldun will be guarding the place heavily with its own troops as well.
You clears out the wolfies yet?
Thanks for your help. The healers should be here soon, yes?
I appreciate you bringing word from home, especially from Emeric. I forget how close the city is to us, and the undead make me worry about that.
Thank you for the news from Camlorn. I have a lot of work ahead of me.
Once Gargast is in custody, Aldcroft will be safe once more.
I'm so scared.. what do I do? What do I do?
Tamarus is a good man. He believed in my father, and I believe in him. Do what he asks.. and I think we will live through this.
Guess we helps you, since you kind of helps us!
You have risked your life for a simple town that you do not call home. I owe it to you to at least know the truth of it all.
These Bloody Eyes weird. Something about protecting veal? Why you protect food?
Hah! You see them runs away from me?
We dids it! Doogie sleep well now I think.. thanks much to you!
You've done us all a great favor, friend. Please, speak to Tamarus. I believe it is time he told you the truth.
You fought well. You should join us, as one of our guard!
The battle of the flesh realm has been won for this day, yet the battle within the Veil will always continue.
Since I lost my brother within the Veil, I've searched for purpose.. but today I found it. Thank you, stranger.
So, you're back again? Can't say I am surprised... where would the high and mighty go today?
Warden Godwin gave you a letter? Good enough for me. Where would you like to go?
Feel free to take a look around, traveler!
Thank Arkay you were here. I would have perished alone.
What business would a hero like you have with me?
Thank you for your kind words. I'm going to pray for my father.
I'm sorry, I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
While I appreciate you retrieving my valuables, I can't stand around all day singing your praises. Leave me to my troubles, of which I have plenty, thank you.
We must recover Ranser's body before our enemy puts it out of reach forever.
You have proven useful, to both the Magis Order and Camlorn.
Thank you for your kind words. I'm going to pray for my father.
You retrieve Daloran's coin purse from the body, but it is empty of gold.  What you find instead are a set of well-worn bone dice, and a debtor's slip for an alarming sum.
Have you found the Third Squad's missing soliders?
I now know what we must do. Once again it falls to you, my friend.
Your soul has been fouled by the filth of Cold Harbor. nnYou should rest in Arkay's light.
Hey, it looks like you've killed a bunch of goblins!
I see Wyress Jacinta has sent us a hero. We welcome your help. The poor, tormented spirits of Westtry are quickly becoming a force beyond our control.
You found it!  Please take it to Shaelle.  She's at the big tree, now.
Seeing Westtry in ruins no doubt hastened my parents' deaths.
So you've met Thetis the Poisoner, eh? Lazy as they come, he is.
With heroes like you on our side, we may stand a chance of stopping this war. I must be away, soon, but first I will answer any questions you might have.
That good-for-nothing wastrel!  Hours late as usual... what do you want?
I overheard your conversation with the cleric. You bring grave news.
Madier and I came up through the ranks together. If it wasn't for the burden of command, I'd be with him. I pray he's all right.

You killed him! The Duke of Camlorn is dead because of you. How do you expect to keep all of Glenumbra from falling to the werewolves without his guiding hand?nnDo you really think you can save us now? Do you?
Cleansing the tarn will take a long time, but you're certainly started purifying the land.
So you found the Werereaver. I think the Danains would approve of you using it. Wield it well, <<1>>.
Did you stop the Blackhand necromancers?

Point the amulet at people in Aldcroft. It will reveal if someone is a werewolf or not.nnIt pains me to say this, but pay special attention to the refugees from Camlorn. I don't believe they're all what they appear to be.
Sibellec is unconscious.
Once we find out what is behind the changes to the Mud-cloaked Hags, I shall turn the tide against those who have taken my swamp!
Shava can smell that you've found some humors for her.
We must investigate the Cave of Penance. We must find the Ehlnofic Lens.
Please take my burial vase to Camlorn. It rests to my left.
Faolchu's army is falling before us. Soon, Camlorn will be ours again.
Glad to have another hero guarding our flank. Watch the rotting teeth on those wolves, though. Stendarr only knows where they've been.
We'll handle the rest, and we'll help Camlorn rebuild. I'm certain you now face bigger challenges.
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
I'm sorry, I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
You have a Gravebinder's spirit, friend. I thank you for helping redeem this place.
I'll never be able to repay you for what you've done. nnHowever, I can offer you some advice: don't travel north.nnThings are much worse up that way, or so I hear.
Yes? You look like you've got something on your mind.
Ah, good to see you again, my friend.  Venison stew tonight, you're welcome to join us.
Spriggans roam the forest around the Dresan Ruins. Be careful. Those monsters were nearly the death of us.
Any friend of Wyress Ileana is a friend of mine. What brings you to our camp?
That's the spirit! What have you got?
Have you found a suitable harpy egg?
Never have I seen the spirits of earth, water, and air appear in the same place at the same time. You are truly remarkable!nnPray tell! What knowledge did they bestow?
I hope you were able to stop the Rock Biter's poison from reaching the people of Aldcroft. It would afflict them as it has afflicted us.
Have you harvested some hawthorn seeds for me?
You found him? Why, thank you so much. You should stay a spell. Tomas will be right along with dinner.
Did you find my wife's locket?
You want to ask me about a locket? Where would you have found such a thing?
Could I... be free...?
After the Wyrd Tree is released from its corruption, Angof's power in High Rock will wane.nnAll hope now rests with you, champion.
Thank you for delivering these tools. We'll put them to good use.
I appreciate you delivering those tools. We can't work without them.
Thank you for the tools. I just wish you'd brought us some weapons!
I'm glad to see you alive. Is it done?
Thank you for returning our family ring. It is invaluable.
Soon, we can return home.  Thank you for returning the Wyrd Tree to us.
Are you from the past or the future? The truth is hazy these days.
Home! I can go home again! Blessings of the forest on you, <<1>>!
You must do what you think is right, of course.
Thank you so much for the safe return of my ring. Let me know if there is anything I can ever do for you.
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
I'm sorry, I'm not in the mood to talk right now.
I'm glad to hear you handled the spriggan problem, though I'll probably lose some business because of it.
I am almost certain we have nothing to say to each other at this point.
You will find Melodian Fiannalor to the east of Varyllis, beyond the Stonewake.
Take care not to spill any of the liquor on yoursefl! It may have rather adverse effects.
Excellent work dispatching the Sload, Numinous.
You will find Sapiarch Lilia at the Kinhouse to the south. This road will lead you there.
Do speak to High Kinlord Langdruun at the Felballin Kinhouse. He should know of our successes.
Have you restored the Aquiferi to their subterranean abodes?
Once you have destroyed an Aquiferi Elemental, collect its Pith and bury it in a Fissure.
We have but one more task in front of us - restoring the Lens to its rightful place above the Kinhouse.
I heard they sent you out into the swamp to meet that witch. nnWas she as strange as everyone says she is?
After you've been out in that swamp for a while, you'll probably need a new pair of boots.
I want to help Camlorn anyway I can. nnStill, I don't know how I would have dealt with that witch. She unnerves me.
I heard you helped Sibellec, but at what cost? nnSome say she's as bad as the wolves.
So many strange things live in that swamp. nnWas Sibellec as odd as the Bretons say she is?
The witch helped you? nnThen I guess we're one step closer to getting rid of those confounded refugees.
They say you met Sibellec. nnYou know what my friend said? He said she turned him into a toad!nnDon't worry. He got better.
You say Sibellec isn't all bad? I don't know about that. you wouldn't believe some of the stories I have heard...
You've done so much for us. You went out into the swamp to help us. nnThank you.
Thanks to you, we're fighting one hopeless battle instead of two.
At last! We no longer have the swamp rising up against us. Now we can focus on the real enemy.
Now that we've dealt with the swamp, we should be ready to storm Camlorn.
Is it just me, or are there less of those hideous swamp creatures now?
I'm growing accustomed to this place. I really hope we can help these people.
I heard you met Sibellec. Did she try to eat you?
The Starglass has been echo-instilled? Excellent! It must go to Lalathal at the Kinhouse at once!
The Pallid Devils bombard us night and day. Would that something could be done!
Maormer corruption has surely mazed my senses. I see and smell the bloody prize you carry, but I do not believe it.
Our Varla Lens is returned, and not a moment too soon. For my people and my Kinship, I give you thanks.
Do you hear that, Optimate? The ocean. You have dulled the roar of the Siege Engines. I can hear the crash of the waves once again.
We will not fail Glenumbra.
The Spellfire Pillars must be disabled.
Do you bear the Starglass I've been expecting?
You must be quick to harvest the Discarnates before they cease to be a menace!
Have you checked on my soul gem?
Camlorn won't remain in General Faolchu's clutches for long.
I can't wait to return to fighting something that's easier to get the drop on.
Rolantae waits for you on the knoll to the southeast.
The Chamberlain means well, but he is used to a different living standard than the rest of us.
The Military Camp Apothecary tries her best, but sometimes a good old-fashioned cure is all a patient needs.
Who would you rather trust? A trained apothecary such as myself or someone else?
Have you tried the device yet? Which way did the thief go?
Have you managed to find my former love, Coren? Did you find my locket?
Aha! There can be no doubt, you are Phynaster reborn! A job well done, Numinous.
I sense tragedy....
Leave me so that I may finish what I have am resolved to do.
Can I assist you somehow?
Did you find the grave? Did you honor my father?
You saw her, didn't you. I can see it in your eyes!
Your aid has been invaluable, my dear Optimate. I shall pray that Mara allows me to bless you in the future.
News of our success here will soon reach Alinor. You should return there and seek audience with Queen Ayarynne.
<<1>> returns. Tell me Optimate, what news have you?
Orgnavar is an infernal device of the Sload!
Again, I warn you, simply touching this book will harm you. Only take it if you are ready.
Please, speak with Suuniqwe, she will not listen to me. You will find her to the east, north of the Shadow's shrine.

What happened on the island? I haven't sensed any changes in the Midnight Talisman. Its power remains dormant.nnTell me. Were you unable to make contact with the spirits of the land? Did they refuse to bless you?
Have you spoken to Vendialara? She can be found just north of here, at the space overlooking Studium Vale.
You've returned! Already the vines that choke Cath Bedraud wither and die. I can only pray this means you were successful.
The Numinous returns. Have you the Varla Lens?
Turned to stone, in the Imagerie at least the location is thematically appropriate.
The Orrery will survive this invasion. Thank you for your help.
I am glad you found the survivors of the expedition. I only wish my fears had proven unfounded.
Oh, my. So the Blackhand is harnessing the power the Welkynd stones. It's worse than I thought... if that's even possible.
Blessed arrows! Thank you for bringing those in. We're running low.

Arturo left Daggerfall years ago to make a name for himself. He rarely sent word home to me.nnI want to know what happened. Did he die in that horrible mine? Was he slain in a tavern brawl? Where is my son?
Have you managed to recover my tools, Optimate?
Did you retrieve the talisman? Is it safe?
I can't help but wonder what that catwoman will do now to ruin my life and my work.
You will always be welcome in Varyllis, Optimate.
My apologies, but perhaps I was unclear. Did I not inform you that Battlereeve Nenwe desired to meet you? She is encamped above the Tessellated Shores, along the eastern coast.
The air is thick with the seeds of Angof's corruption. nnWhy are you here?
Vines clog my veins and film stains my eyes. nnWhy are you here?
My body aches with corruption, strangled by choking tendrils of hate. nnWhy are you here?
I hope my notes proved useful to Scholar Lael at the Dwynnarth Ruins.
It's not easy waiting out here until they're all safe, but somebody needs to keep track of the survivors.
<<1>> will get more chickens someday. That evil man cannot stop <<1>> from having many, many chickens!
I haven't heard any bellyaching from Gulitte or Al'kari in the past hour. That's a relief.nnI take it you've handled their dispute?
How goes the hunt, <<1>>?
I must admit, I did not think you would best the mighty Kirin. Truly you have proven yourself, <<1>>.

I heard someone searching through my things the other night. Gave me quite a scare. I thought it was one of those spriggans!nnThe next day, I heard the Thierry family's ring was stolen. Do you think there's a connection?
<<1>>, do you have any more information on the Red Rook bandits?
<<1>>, do what you can to take back the tower. My people will aid you if they can.
If you enter the ruins, don't go alone. Bring help.
The Ascendants are trapped in this tower. You may free them by using the Pyxis of Ashes.
It's good to see you back safe. Did you find the caps I asked for?

Once you have recovered the pieces of the crown I ask that you take them to Talrien the Archivist, who toils within the bowels of the Umbral Tower. The building sits on a lone island along the southern edge of the bay.nnYou may go now.
You did well to stop the Great Elum, but I fear it was the least of our concerns. Much more urgent problems still threaten High Rock.
You would make a great addition to the Fighters Guild.
Can I assist you somehow?
Ah, the Serpent's killer. What can I interest you in today?
Nirn brightens the Orrery once again. You know not what joy you inspired.
If only you could understand what you have for the Skyharkers.  May your Ancestors protect you!
Ah, our champion. For every turn of Auri-El may your name be praised.
You have returned hope to us in a dark time.
The Dawnshards continue to renew my magicka. Thank you again, Numinous.
With the Varline to Alinor restored, we may catch up on the latest court gossip.
Shannae is still not entirely herself. But she is more herself than she has been for some time.
The noise goes through me. It smells like dirt and old blood. I shut my eyes and I can see it. Purple. Writhing.
The beast this feather came from must have been a sight to behold!
Any luck finding my pickaxe? My father gave it to me, and I can't go back to work without one.
I have inspected the stone.
Be wary! The dead rise from the waves even now!
By the fiery gaze of Auriel, slay the Maormer scum!
With the siege engines of Sunhold silenced, surely we will push the Maormer off Sunhold.
Fivefold venerations, Optimate. Welcome back to Alinor!
It is an unmitigated pleasure to see you once again, my dear Numinous.
The Queen awaits you inside.
The Maormer have barricaded this bridge. We stand guard here against any further incursions.
Can you not see that we are under siege here?
Those foul cadavers have no place in our gardens, nor anywhere on Summerset! Destroy them swiftly, Optimate.
Hail, <<1>>. It is well that Kinlady Genivra sent you, for this is not a task to undertake alone.
Sunhold Island lies directly south of here. Infiltrate the Maormer camps and destroy their supplies!
We keep a careful watch on the movements of Maormer troops.
Keep a watchful eye out for Maormer infiltrators.
Soon enough we shall retake Sunhold.
The destruction of the siege engines on Sunhold will reduce injuries around the Kinhouse and the gardens. My job, of course, will be no easier.
When you have lit the Isque Rose Incense before the altar, we will begin the ceremony.
Bless you for what you've done. I don't know what I'd do if I lost my husband.
I will take Roberte to jail myself. Perhaps I can plead our case to them instead.
Would you favor us by playing the Sacred Instrument near at hand? Be not bashful.
Such a vision you are. What brings you to my Shrine, my dear Numinous?
What? What? What? Too slow! What?
Have you tried the device yet? Which way did the thief go?
Do you seek battle, Optimate? By the Might of Trinimac, I swear you shall find it on this beach.
Battle calls us, Numinous. The Maormer must be defeated!
I will stay here a moment to regain my strength before taking my leave.
My companion awaits you west of here, near the border of the Orrery. May Auri-El be your guide.
Travel swiftly to the Orrery. Vartisan Urselor awaits your arrival.
There are more zombies coming up the banks and the Oyinaam needs to be protected! Careful of their explosive nature.
There are more zombies coming up the banks and the Oyinaam needs to be protected! Careful of their explosive nature.
There are more zombies coming up the banks and the Oyinaam needs to be protected! Careful of their explosive nature.
There are more zombies coming up the banks and the Oyinaam needs to be protected! Careful of their explosive nature.
The matter of the Varla Lens is important, Optimate. Do try not to fumble it.
Perfection is all around you, Optimate. You need only know how to look for it.
Praise to you, Optimate! Take the carapaces to Vartisan Urselor in the Orrery as soon as you are able.
Auri-El at last! I'll be adding a few special touches of my own. You, perhaps, will appreciate them.
Perhaps another could answer your questions, Optimate.
May the Exemplars protect you, Optimate.
May the ancestors protect you, Optimate.
If you were unable to return Nirn, we would have simply made a new Varla Lens.nnWell done, I suppose.
Honor and praise to you. I regret that you must find us in such a trying hour.
Honor and praise to you. I regret that you must find us in such a trying hour.
There is much work to be done now, with the Discarnate Servitors run amok.
The soldiers say that there is one less Giant Sea Serpent in our waters because of you. I suppose that merits a congratulation.
Praise to you, noble Numinous!
May the Exemplars protect you, Optimate.
May the Exemplars protect you, Optimate.
Why have you come here?
I must thank you for your level head in this matter.
A foul daedra has stolen the voice of the lovely Priestess Isrisa. Truly, such creatures have no love of beauty.
I heard of your deeds in the Fane. Perhaps the Queen was not rash in her choice to name you an Optimate.
I'm certain Duke Nathaniel resents my success at Alcaire Castle. nnIf it wasn't for Duchess Lakana, he would have run me out of here by now.

Maelys is in the Lion Guard. She's gone to the farms to find proof of my innocence.nnPlease find her! She's the only one who isn't out to get me. She's the only one who can help me.nnYou aren't out to get me, are you?
Praise and honor to you, Optimate. May Mara bless you on your travels.
In all things, there are those who lead, and those who serve. Neither is less an honor.
I knew Dabienne Vanne wasn't in league with these evil creatures. She's a good woman and a loyal friend.
Surely the Eight sent you to save us. Me, my daughter, we owe you our lives. nnDo you always go to such great lengths to help people you don't even know?
Inwold must know something. Find out what. We're wasting time.
No one can replace Duchess Lakana... but thank you for bringing the man who murdered my mistress to justice.
Please consider my words. <<1>> could not keep order in this city without my intervention.nnIf he's left to lead the city after the fighting ends, it will fall.
They could be anywhere. I just hope they're all right.
You've blessed us all with your generosity. My family won't forget this!
I can see it in your eyes. I'm turning. Becoming one of those  things.nnNo! I refuse to give in to despair! I want to live, gods damn it! I want to live!

Finnegan's not the type to renege on his word. I fear the worst.nnLook for Finnegan and Cray along the northern road. It leads through the Wracked Plain to Shornhelm. You may run into survivors of the last battle. Help any of our people you can.

I am not a fool. We can't win this war without aid, yet I will not sit here twiddling my thumbs while every fool with a weapon endlessly contemplates whether to fight or flee.nnTake up arms or stay out of the way.
Interrogate Fahjiri. Find out what she knows. I cannot do it - I do not trust myself not to strangle her.
Trader's Meet hasn't seen much custom since the fighting started, but there should be someone down there to talk with. Just follow the road west.
Alcaire's paranoia is fading, but many plots remain hidden.nnI will not fail my liege again.
Where's Sir Hughes? I haven't seen him for a while.nnIn fact, I haven't seen any of the Knights of the Flame lately.

I have yet to hear news from anyone in <<1>>. I have no idea how they fare.nnThe Mages Guild is spread too thinly across Rivenspire, if you ask me. Of course, it's not my place to plan our strategies. Excuse me while I return to my books.

I don't know who I really am any more. Part of me is still alive, in agony. A part of that  abomination!nnIf Reezal-Jul were in front of me right now, I swear my hate alone would tear that lizard to shreds!

Why do you delay? A case of fear hasn't come over you, has it? nnLady Eselde eagerly waits back in town. Strike down Montclair, and House Tamrith will raise Shornhelm to newfound glory!nnDo this, and you will truly be a champion of House Tamrith.
You've thinned the number of corrupted nereids here, but they'll keep coming back until the source of their corruption is destroyed.
Going through the village, are you? nnChecking to see who's home and who's out, are you? nnAre you planning to come back to rob everyone?nnI'm keeping a close eye on you, stranger. A very close eye.
One of the thieves dropped a note that will prove Aunt Dabienne's innocence.nnI put the note in my diary, but I never thought our farm would be attacked.
I knew Inwold wouldn't leave me. nnNo matter what other manifestations of insanity infect this place, Invold would never leave me.
Your words have moved me. I can overcome this. nnPlease tell <<1>> I'm all right. I don't have the strength to face anyone in <<2>> right now.
I apologize for the mess. Master Ahtah's study was recently ransacked.
Any news about the health of the merchants in Alcaire?

Magharz' scouts sent you, didn't they? nnI told him to let me go. I can't allow him to be shamed in front of his people. nnWe were foolish. Everyone makes mistakes, but rarely do they cost so much. nnHe must let me go.
Don't forget. We're watching you.
I see you've found Inwold's secret. He refused to show those poems to Dabienne - but he could not part with them, either.
We wouldn't have survived without your help. Thank you.
I can feel the pull of his influence. The closer I get to the cave, the more control he has over me.
There is still another soul that needs your help. Seek out <<1>> near the town square. Help him get over his grief.nnOnce all the defender spirits have assembled, we can end this once and for all.
Montclair should suffer, just as he made others suffer from the blood fever.
Whoever <<1>> is, he must be stopped. nnI won't let him terrorize all of Rivenspire with his undead horde!

I knew more of my fellow knights would come to see the insanity Sir Croix means to unleash at Alcaire Castle. nnI think we have enough knights now to retake the keep. I've sent them to take up strategic positions.
Moira's Hope has been destroyed? nnSeems like we're on our own. We'll make it  somehow.
Now that the poor soul's body has melted a bit, it is easy enough to retrieve the artifact from his grasp.
Testing random greeting text to see if the text cuts off or appears corrupted.

Sometimes they treat me as though I were a child! I may be new to this life, but I'm nobody's child!nnWell, except for my mother. And my father, I guess. But that's besides the point. You better go and catch up with Verandis.
Blood and glory, my friend. Blood and glory!
Huh? All three of you are buying me an ale? I thank you all!
How goes your treasure hunting? Any fantastic Aldmeri treasure, yet?
I'm glad we could help each other. May the Divines walk with you, friend.
It is good to see you returned safe, my friend. Did S'Rashi yield any useful information?
The moors will always be haunted, but thanks to you, I won't have to shout to be heard over the spirits' wailing.nnI suppose my wife, Frelie, will be expecting me to help defend the town now.
I allowed my Duchess to be murdered in our her own bedroom. I have failed my Duke and all Alcaire.nnI pray to Akatosh I am allowed to redeem myself.
I hope this is the right decision. I'd be lying if I said I didn't still have some reservations, but I suppose this'll at least give me a chance to earn some coin.
I never thought Julien would feel the same way I do.nnThis isn't a trick, is it? I'm a blacksmith. I have a hammer, you know.
The talisman and the power it represents has corrupted countless hearts and minds.nnIt is a blight upon this world and the ones who would wield it.
The weakness is spreading.... nnPlease, stop them before it's too late!
Well? Now that the foolish experiment with the braziers has failed, has the king come to see reason? Does he realize this fight cannot be won?
S'rashi wants to help Captain Marck too, but S'rashi must pay Midnight Union boss, yes?nnHelp S'rashi get the money he needs and all will be well.
Sounds like you've got an even livelier party than usual in there.
They're whooping it up even more than usual in there.
Go on, get to the game! We have so little time left. nnOh, I do hope you have fun!
It was a pleasure to do business with you. Please, return and visit me in a few years. I'd love for you to see my new pet!
Stay alert, citizen.
The people here are so uncooperative. You'd think that after all Wayrest has done for them, they would show a little more respect.nnI'm of the opinion that we'll never recover the Crown of Shornhelm!

The Bloodsworn lurk in the chambers and corridors of the Doomcrag. They're followed closely by their guardians. nnBe sure to rid them of their guards first, lest you find yourself facing creatures even you could not defeat.
You've done what no mortal man has done. You've entered Cold Harbor and returned alive.
Is someone there? I can't see you.nnEverything's so dark.
You've done it!  Now all you must do is take Ranser's crown, and put us all at last to rest.
You did it! You made it in time! I don't know what we would've done without you.
My ritual worked, didn't it? I felt it. Azura's messenger came to you, just as she came to me.nnShe will save Gavaudon. She will save us all!

It's bad outside these walls, but Shornhelm isn't faring much better. Political warfare on the inside, disease-ridden beasts on the outside.... nnYou go on ahead, I'll make sure Finn's wounds are treated.
Please, leave me to my grief. Let me mourn my wife.
I heard what happened to the Nirine woman. Thank the heavens you were there to talk some sense into that poor, crazed man.
Tell that so-called doctor... if I see him again, I will not hold back. For now, I just want to be with my Charlotte.
I appreciate your gesture, but I can't leave Tahn. nnNow get out of here before someone catches you.
Be careful in Baelbrone. The Fervor has driven the people there to rampant excess.
Aphren's Hold is west of here, along the road that connects Wayrest to Bangkorai.nnI will meet you there.
You are the one Tahra spoke of. Let us see this map.
You're the one with the map, yes? Tahra mentioned you. Come, let's see it!
Ah, you are the one with the map! Tahra informed me of your coming. Let us see it, hm?
You live? Appearances can be deceiving, it would seem.nnWell done. Lady Eslede waits to speak to you. For House Tamrith!
Stay safe. You are destined for great things, but if you fall prey to this evil, I fear we will follow you into the darkness.
Borkul has already dispatched some Blackmauls to Wayrest for supplies.
Follow the beach south. Walk around to the west to find <<1>>. nnIf you don't take the long way around, you'll find yourself fighting through a horde of Imperials.nnForewarned is forearmed!
Fine work. Now, deliver the Moondrop Mold to Aenlin at the Sunlight Stair to the northeast.
Were you able to convince the Swamp Cypress to move off the road? It is to the north and impossible to miss.
You have potential, my friend. nnThe Grand Gladiator is looking forward to fighting you.
Lord Moric doesn't pay me to deal with your problems. nnGet lost, or you'll have one more.
Grul's already in the arena, poppet! nnHe's looking forward to splitting your skull.
My fellow! How do you do?
You smell terrible. nnWait! You must have the samples I requested. Yes?
Where's Heloise? Is she all right? Does she need help?
Hey. Funny kind of luck I have, eh?
The Swamp Cypress appears to be hovering over a fallen Seedling - protecting it. One of its branches is extended, pointing to a Mound of Dirt to the east.
The Swamp Cypress creaks.
Look along the northern shore for any useable equipment.nnBe careful of the crocs, though. The scent of fresh blood has drawn more of them.nnThey're frenzied and voracious.
I would not wish my fate on anyone, but I am powerless to stop it.
You'll find a bunch of Imperials west of Southpoint. nnYou should be able to identify them by their incredibly ugly mugs.
Did Baron Dorell ask you to take care of those bastards, Juberic and Orlozag? He was livid when I told him about their defection to House Montclair.
The guardian spirit of the Bonebarrows was once a Bosmer named King Faume Toad-Eye.nnI can't imagine he is happy about the Bretons despoiling his home.

Ah, you are the one my husband spoke of. Somehow, I knew you would find your way here.nnIt's a pity you've found us this way, waiting about like lambs for the slaughter. We will not fall without taking the whole of this accursed place with us!
You seem like a nice enough sort. I'm sure you didn't mean to cause so much trouble.nnSummoning Daedra, however....nnIf you're going to do that, young one, you'll make the wrong kind of friends.
Got them all, did you? What a sport! Most people give up after the first sapping.
Follow each tunnel in this pit to a room.nnThen destroy the infernal device core you find inside it. nnHack it, blast it, kick it... it doesn't matter as long as you destroy it!
Please, find the rest of the Hinaults. They couldn't have gone far.nnAnd remember, if any of them have been killed, you need to burn their bodies and collect their ashes.
The Swamp Cypress towers over a fallen Seedling, as if protecting it. A branch of this tree is extended, pointing to a Mound of Dirt to the east.
My hands will glow for weeks from handling all this Moondrop.
I cannot allow one who committed so grevious a crime to ever serve me again.

You'll find Godrun within the dungeon, unaware of how his actions are affecting not only Stormhaven, but the Daggerfall Covenant itself.nnUse the potion near him so both of you will fall asleep. Then enter his dream to find and kill the Omen.
I ran Gerard out of town, so he wouldn't continue his deplorable scavenging. nnPerhaps I'll have to do the same with Manard.
Yes, I think you did it. The Barrows should begin to settle down now. All that's left is to send Marienne on her way.
Have you decided to accuse me of something even more terrible, darling? Did I kick that poor man's puppy, perhaps?
Without you, I would not be here, carrying my former master's staff.  Thank you again for your help.
My boy... my poor boy. What did he ever do wrong?
You tell the Prince everything I said, you hear me? All right, then. Go on with you.

If Ayarynne places her trust in you, so do I. The Camoran throne is rightfully mine, yet everywhere I find loyalties divided.nnI need to find those who would support me. Be my voice in this city. Speak with the Treethanes; convince them of our cause.
How repugnant! The smell of burning flesh lingers. nnSoon cold winds will rush across the moors and drive away that horrific stench.
Christophe was a fool, but I'm overjoyed to see him alive. I know Makana doesn't approve - but you saved him too. The three of us will learn to live together.
You've given back my memory, my sister, my nephew, and even Christophe. Thank you. I suppose now I must live with their union - and watch them like a hawk.

The corpses are north of Oldgate, at the <<1>>. Use the <<2z>> I gave you on them. You can also use it on yourself to repel bloodfiends for a short time.nnLet <<3>> know when you're done. He's in the old tower in the middle of the Farm.
I'm impressed. Verandis was right about you, yet again. nnThat man has an uncanny way of sensing things.
They want you to think they have locked me in. I have locked them out!
Have you found them out, these rebels and traitors? Have you dealt with them appropriately?
Nothing like Sun's Dusk Ale. Nothing like it around here, anyway.
Don't believe a word he says.nnHe's stealing my cattle. I know it!
Push off, or I'll knock your head in.
We're closed. Come back later.
Did you find a way to help me?
The townsfolk may not agree with everything I've put forth, but if they see you endorsing this, they may reconsider their position. nnYou've brought peace to Fell's Run. People trust you.
Trust cannot be earned overnight. I'll do my part to keep the peace in Fell's Run. nnPerhaps I'll even live to see the day when we aren't in conflict.
What do you want from me now, lackey of Wayrest?nnPerhaps you'll steal my shoes next!
The stench of dead fish and bloodied Imperials. nnYou visit us from Southpoint, do you not?
Get out of my sight.
Excellent news! Now inform Canonreeve Sorcassil of your success. You will find him in the Thalmor.
Step into the dream world and bring me Galthis' head, or my plague of Omens upon Stormhaven will never end.
You've done what no mortal man has done. You've entered Cold Harbor and returned alive.

Please don't let Verandis know about this. He'd be outraged if he knew I was dabbling in the arts of dark magic. nnOh, and if you forget where the items come from, check the list!nnYou're doing this in the name of love. Remember that!
One of our patrols found Tristan sprawled in the tunnels outside of here. nnHe uttered few cryptic words before he slipped into a deep sleep. nnHe hasn't awakened since.
Please take that wickwheat to Makar. Your praises will be sung for generations for saving our horses.
