I see your arms are full, and I recognize the sacks you're carrying. nnYou found my things! What a relief.
Did you deal with the Ogre Patriarchs?
Maybe the people in Fell's Watch will pay more attention to what their young people are doing.nnThat would solve many of their problems.
I'd never felt this much wind before we came to Elden Root.
I knew there were loyalists there! Be sure to give the list of names to Battlereeve Hanen.
I think a message has been sent to the Imperials. Don't you agree, <<1>>?

The loyalists within Leaftower have already supplied us with valuable intelligence. Life is going to become difficult for the Imperials.nnAnd after they're gone, life will become difficult for their collaborators.

The corsairs don't know you. Your audience with the duchess won't raise questions. My lady's manor is the grandest in Northpoint's main square.nnBe sure to speak with the chancellors before you intrude on her. Brann and Yvette are quite protective.
Can't let a bad apple or three ruin the barrel. At least, that's what I hear.
It seems you wound up saving me twice. nnI wish I knew a proper way to express my level of gratitude.

I lost my mother years ago during Ranser's War. That bracelet is all I have to remember her by. I must get it back.nnI understand the dangers that await you in the northern district. nnI'll pay you well. I promise.
I hope Duzug leaves me alone after this.nnShe got what she wanted. So much for justice.
Thank you for restoring me to the throne.nnIf Northpoint prospers, it is because of you.
Leave me, please.

I know only of the whispers between Montclair's guard regarding this resistance. You'd best check around town for information, perhaps in the inn?nnPlease hurry. My time runs short and already the urge of the bloodlust aches from within.
The rumors were true. Amazing.
The Blood Fever is becoming more common these days. Somehow we haven't all caught it yet.
I thought my son would carry on the family duties when I retired. I never thought I'd outlive him.nnHave you found Elise? She's the only one I have left.
Have you retrieved the reports from the scouts yet? I do hope they have not eaten my quality paper, or something other such nonsense.
Don't worry. I'll see you in Northpoint by sunrise... pitchfork in hand.
Someone stole from me.nnI think I can make a good guess who it was.
Someone stole from me. nnI think I can guess who it was.
Her Vampire servants fill the basin on the altar with blood. They summon her to her chambers. nnWhere they get the blood, I don't want to know!
Have you found Verandis yet?  I wouldn't ignore a summons from the leader of the Ravenwatch.
Godrun never used to be so obsessed with guarding this dam.
Ho ho! What chaos! nnBaan Dar himself would be proud of such madness!
Have you found Verandis yet? I wouldn't ignore a summons from the leader of the Ravenwatch.
You must travel to the northeast and enter Gil-Var-Delle through the tunnel. There you will find Black Log and in the hollow center of the tree Dark Carcass.nnKill him.
I tried to help, but the bloodfiends were too much for me.
How repugnant, the smell of burning flesh. Soon the winds shall sweep the moors and drive away the taint.
Ready yourself. The vampires will not hold back.
We need more grisly bits to make the scarecrows look like dead harpies.
I just know what my wife is going to say. Too much beef and potatoes, not enough greens.nnUgh. Greens! Cows eat greens. Men eat cows. That's the way of the world.nnAnd vampires eat men, I suppose.

Yes? You've done your deed for me. Is there another reason you crave my attention? Is it my lovely charm? Is it my exceedingly good looks? nnRegardless, you've done what I've asked. You'd best be on your way. There's always another battle to win.
I've heard about you.nnBrave, they say, and resourceful!nnYou know, things aren't always as they seem. I could tell you a thing or two.
I don't believe we have any more to say to each other, <<1>>. Good day.nnI said, "Good day!"
You made it. Were you able to light the signal fire?
I can't thank you enough. I will prove myself worthy of your mercy.
Can you help me? I don't want to die here.
Why must we always realize our feelings too late? nnWhy do we always lose the ones we love... without the chance to tell them we love them?nnI... I can't think straight right now. I'm sorry.
More innocents lost....nnWe have to end this. Now.
Perhaps I have made misjudged your character, <<1>>.nnI don't make mistakes when leaking information.
You've retrieved all the statues? Magnificent artifacts, are they not?nnWith those glittering eyes, they almost look alive....nnForgive me. My imagination is getting out of hand.
If the Shornhelm Guard can't clear the roads, they should let the Fighters Guild take care of it. We know how to get things done.
You may go ahead without me. I shall meet you in front of the Kinhouse shortly.
I find myself taken by a curious desire to sculpt our Mistress myself. I mean, an actual sculpture. Not turn her to stone!
It was wise of me to not chip a piece off of Ameralee.
Go!  nnKill those crabs before your time's up! They're all along the beach! nnOh, and you should be careful of those Nords, I supppose.
Go! Kill those crabs before your time's up! nnThey're all up and down the beach from here. nnOh, and careful of those Nords too, I suppose.
Simply place the Altmer Books in the shelves around me. Worry not, I'll orgnaize them later. I won't make you watch.
Thank you so much for the safe return of my ring. Let me know if there is anything I can ever do for you.
Thanks to your help, my job is made eaiser.
I see you've brought a fair amount of materials back with you! Let's have a look at them.

We don't have many nice things handed down in our family, so I'm not worried. Still, it's sad to think that someone would steal the Thierry's family heirloom. nnHope someone catches that evil-doer soon.
I pray you bring good news...
I am intrigued by you mortals. Entertain me and I will return Isrisa's voice
I've been praying to Stendarr that you would be back soon. How was the hunt?
Stay alert, citizen.
The words do not frighten me any more. But I do not think I will return to the Tower of Many Bindings.
If we only had a few more men, we could teach those Bitterkites a lesson ourselves.
I hoped success would include your safe return. Welcome back.
Was it difficult to restore the Var Lens?

Are you ready for glory, Lieutenant? Our greatest hour is at hand. Those green-skinned beasts think they have us defeated; they'll soon realize how incredibly wrong they are.nnHave the contents of Reezal-Jul's packets been poured into the braziers?
This was the last of the Kinlords, <<1>>. We have secured approval of the Queen's policies from all the Kinships of Summerset.nnTime to return to Alinor, eh?
Do not travel too far south, Optimate. The Maormer bombard our lands from the sea.
M-mother? nnI can't... I can't see you.
The Red Rooks' camp is north of here. nnYou should take a uniform from one of their cold dead bodies. After all, it wouldn't hurt to have a disguise.
It is fortunate that the Scintillants of Dusk are skilled in vulgar art of forging. They have need of weapons with Maormer landings on two shores.
As amusing as this will presently be, I promise I will try not to laugh.
Well done, my friend! The Lord Magister will be anxious to speak with you.
The witch helped us? Excellent! But at what cost?
The Numinous returns. Have you the Varla Lens?
What do you want? Can't you see I'm grieving?
Leave me be. I have nothing to say to anyone.
The Lion Guards talk a lot, but I've yet to see them do something worthwhile.
Why are you bothering me? Can't you see I'm busy?
I feel so much safer in Aldcroft since the Lion Guard arrived. nnWhen they leave, it'll be a sad day for us.nnSad for us, but happy for Camlorn, I guess.
This was the last of the Kinlords, <<1>>. We have secured approval of the Queen's policies from all the Kinships of Summerset.nnTime to return to Alinor, eh?
This was the last of the Kinlords, <<1>>. We have secured approval of the Queen's policies from all the Kinships of Summerset.nnTime to return to Alinor, eh?
This was the last of the Kinlords, <<1>>. We have secured approval of the Queen's policies from all the Kinships of Summerset.nnTime to return to Alinor, eh?
I have lost everything. My home. My ships. My discarnates.
I pray your visit to the Menagerie be informative and enjoyable.

While we formulate our strategies against Montclair, your presence has been requested by the Mages Guild. nnMake haste. Fulfill the favors they ask of you, so you may return to supporting the people of Shornhelm.
We continue to seek a breach in the castle to reach Montclair. For now, the Mages Guild requests your assistance. When you are done with your matters with them, return to us.
Praise Mara and praise to you, <<1>>!nnThis creature is more beautiful than I could have ever dreamt.
Just take a handful and sling it where you want them to go! nnThey'll eat it quickly, so keep slinging the feed until they go where you want them.
I pray your visit to the Menagerie be informative and enjoyable.
Can't trust anyone these days. We have to be careful!
What did Irne decide? Will he drop his accusations against Govran?
If flour production is to continue in Alcaire these cogs must be restored.
Well, this is certainly an interesting turn of events. I'm at a loss for words.
Any luck? nnIf you can find out who shut down the lighthouse and bring them to justice, you'll clear my name.
If we lock up any more villagers, the entire town will be empty.
What do you think is really in that ship's cargo? nnWhy do they want to unload it so badly?nnWhy am I talking to you?
If they'd let us unload this ship, we'd have work to do. It's the constable and deputies that are making us lose our day's wages.
That poor soldier. He swore he would just scout the area and return immediately. He didn't intend to fight alone.nnI'll need to tell his family.
Ah, my Ganise is such a fickle bird, but such a necklace must surely impress her!
We've sailed into Koeglin Village's port many times in the past. It's got a good, deep harbor.nnIf people in the village knew we needed their help, I'm sure they'd come to our aid.
It's not easy work, but it's profitable.
Sir Edmund is the leader we need to see us through this hard time.
We've had many strange events near Alcaire lately. I don't go anywhere unless I have my weapon at my side.
It's impossible to know who to trust these days.
Thank you for speaking with my mistress. nnI can't be seen leaving the grounds of the keep. That would arouse suspicion.
Please, do not speak with me! The Duke thinks all are against him, but it is not true. They are all against me!
Those pirates are brutes! Don't let them take me.
It is impossible to know who to trust these days.
You brought down Cruor. Thank you.
The Dominion is stronger with you among us.
I see an abundance of smoke drifting away from the beach. nnI imagine our Bosmer friend Tiradil was successful?
My family's always sold provisons to ships. Colane Oscent had no business stopping me.nnI'm glad to be rid of those chickens, although my husband doesn't see it that way.

I shouldn't have run... I should have waited.nnWe thought it'd be safe in the woods to the east of town. Always hide there when pirates or Maormer come looting.nnThe Imperials dragged them away to the east.
Have you found them? nnIs it as bad as I thought? nnDid the demons get them?
You have the treacherous evil Imperial Captain's lockbox? Good. Gooooood.nnLet me see it, quickly!
Do I bother you at your business? Take a walk!
Do you mind? I'm trying to do some business here.
Mother used to sit beside the riverbank during her nightly walks. nnShe liked listening to the water.nnI hope you find her. My sister Ganise is a terrible cook, and we're all suffering.

I had to jump ship in the middle of the night and swim ashore. Thank goodness there weren't any horrible things in the water.nnCaptain Veronika said she's never known this town to be so unfriendly. I hope you can clear things up with her.
Well, this one thinks it a shame to let so much fine armor go to rust on the seashore.
Bravosi has much to answer for, but I will not be the one who judges him. nnI've ordered him sent to the Tribunal Temple in Kragenmoor, where his callous dealings will be redressed.
If you have nothing more, I must attend to more important matters. nnReturn to me after you've slain this Argonian rabble-rouser.nnI shall reward you handsomely.

I do not trust the words of the Dres Councilor. His House would profit from the fall of Davon's Watch rather than its recovery. And his hatred of our fellow races within the Pact makes me question his sincerity.
This battlefield is ripe for the plucking! Many in Valenwood would pay good coin for these... abandoned articles.

How does Miluru expect me to work with that ruffian? Truly, I thought that Bravosi's methods were asinine, but I can't imagine a country Argonian to know a whit about managing a city, much less a city with as many problems as we!
They say you killed a hundred Imperials and General Cruor cowered before you!
All of the Houses are vigilant against any suspected carriers of Blight, but House Dres has been most vocal as to rooting out the source.
I hear you brought some eels in, eh? Oh, look at the big hero, saving us from starvation! And who thinks of the old eelmer, eh? Eh?nnDamned foreigners, coming in and taking our jobs....
Stealing from the dead in our most sacred gravesite deserves more than the merciful release of death. nnTheir spirits will serve Othrenis for penance.
The cliff racers have been nesting in the fort, to the east.  I would look for their nests in high places.
It is not safe for you here. Leave this city - return to Priest Velanda, and I will join you there.
Marea will not rest until I am destroyed. nnWhen she finds out you haven't done that, she'll arrive to do it herself.nnWill you protect me, stranger? She could arrive at any moment.
You must kill Sir Croix, or all of this bloodshed will have been in vain.
Despite what he's done, I still hold Sir Hughes in the highest regard.nnPlease don't judge him too harshly.
Can it be that you have succeeded?
It was once profitable to have all the shipping in Ebonheart go through my hands, but now my product is threatened.
Sera Orvona would never condone resorting to violence or anything... illegal to reclaim these items - but then again, we know better than to ask questions.

Try and put a little quickness into your step there, would you? There are a lot of people out for me in Alcaire right now. The sooner I can pack this stuff up and get out of here, the less I have to worry about my head leaving my shoulders.
Ahjiivi cannot aid you in your chase. Many slaves suffer from this Blight. Ahjiivi will watch their captors die before her very eyes.
There was a lot of shouting in town the other day. People screaming, burning things.nnI caught a fish that day!
As if the Imperials weren't bad enough. Now we have to worry about our own traitorous kin.

A thousand favors upon you, my dear friend. I look forward to the safe return of my pilfered pantaloons. nnThe wine token concealed in my pants pocket has special significance to me, I assure you. Also, I did not need to pay full-price for it.
Just open the chest right up, dear. It's not locked.
Move on. I'm trying to work here.
Were you trained as an entertainer in your youth, perhaps? Your movements seemed quite natural and fluid.
I sense a darkness lifted from the fiery depths.nnTell me, have you done the deed?
I don't like to boast, but like you, I am a magnificent dancer.nnI just prefer to save my best dancing for the privacy of my own home.nnI should... show you sometime.
I'm still in awe of your dancing prowess, friend! Someday, I hope to be as good a performer as you.
You're a good person, my dear, and a great dancer.
Good news! Moments ago, animals stampeded out into the Thrambles.nnNow have enough food to feed Razorvine for a long time!
By the by, I feel compelled to warn you that the Spriggarum has not exactly been tested yet....

Normally slouchbears keep to themselves. The city folk even raise them to pull carts and such.nnThe slouchbears in the Thrambles are feral. They'll attack you on sight. Fortunately, they don't get along with the hoarvor or the thunderbugs.
Did you say something about poisonous meat? nnI just ate some. nnHey, at least it was a fresh kill.
There's so much that needs to be done. I'll take care of my duties soon... eventually... but not right now.
They say we owe you, <<1>>, and I am one to repay my debts.nnThank you for what you've done in Menevia!
Would you go down the corridor and check the snare trap? nnYou should see if it caught something big, slobbering, and dangerous. nnJust in case, of course.
There is no time to waste. Find the dens and spread the poison, else the lamia may devour everyone in Reywell.
Have you slain those foul creatures? Have you made them scream?nnI can't stand them, but I like it when they die screaming.
Now I can sneak in and out of here at will, pretending to be one of the prisoners.nnThe others will wish they were as clever as me. Your help was exactly what I needed!
I don't know what's been going on around here, but life seems a lot nicer. nnPeople aren't so afraid any more.nnI like living in Alcaire.
You avenged us, <<1>>.nnThank you!
The Empire will crumble under the foot of the Southpoint Avenger.
What's your birthsign, stranger? I was born under the sign of the Lover.nnThe stars aligned for our brief assignation. Would you dare to kiss me now?
As far as I'm concerned, every day is Heart's Day. nnIf only there were an inn nearby....
Let's not waste any time. I can't let my friends walk around dead any longer.
They'll store packages in the cellars as soon as they get to the fort. nnThe guards in the cellars might attack you. nnBe quick, but if you must fight, then fight.
You have the <<1>>s?
Swimming to the wrecked ship to the south. nnCollecting somethng shiny, something pointy, something clangy, and something round!nnThe stimulus of competition! The certainty of reward!
My ears are ringing. I never noticed how strident Lady Diane can be when her passions are stirred.
This will show that unscrupulous ruffian what it means to interfere with one of my celebrations. Knock his teeth in!
Remembering our last visitor. nnHearing of her perils. nnThe horror of running from thunderbugs! The pain of many injuries!nnDiscoveirng Ookvoot. Great joy.

I smell... gold. Lots of gold. Only a nose of nobility, so refined in its senses, could smell something so pure and rich. You will assist me in... reacquiring it, yes? Surely such a lowly citizen as you would wish to aid one such as I.
Are you ready to go? Will you please get me out of here?
Have you spoken to the Foreman or Sulen the Tailor?  Sulen is here in Kragenmore, to the south of here.  You can find the Foreman somewhere on the Blightfence to the northeast.
There's much that needs to be done! I'll have to go home soon and do it all... but not just yet.
Those slave traders are spreading throughout Stormhaven, or so I've heard.
If you're looking for the Blighted, they're everywhere.  All around the Conclave, demanding our help.
This one is glad the slavers' blood feeds the soil.
I hope nothing else horrid crawls out of the sea to ruin my fishing trip.nnWhat's next? Sea serpents? Mermen? Maybe my children will come to vist.nnAll I wanted was a little peace and quiet.

I'll need to resend the invitations. I do hope Lord Dalon doesn't host a gathering of his own! That would severely hamper the impact of my event. I'll also need to invite Lady Malnith.... nnYes? Why are you still here? I have a festival to plan!
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in someone's skull.
There is no greater feeling than bashing in your opponent's skull!
Your soul is foul with the filth of Cold Harbor. nnYou should rest in Arkay's light.
Hoom is filled with warm appreciation for your efforts. nnThe pleasure of your acquaintance!
The courage of the victor! The well-deserved congratulations!nnPraising the stranger! nnAccepting the stranger as a friend.
Admiring the <<1>>. nnWill the <<1>> be meeting Wud at Elder Knonk's hut?nnGiving the prize to the stranger!
Meeting the <<1>> at Elder Knonk's hut. nnAwarding the <<1>> the prize!
Is it true the Imperials have been driven out of Haven? Can we go home now?
I was told the problems in Haven were solved.nnSurely that was mistaken? I still can't get a decent glass of wine.
Bring me three Hammerdeath Victory Tokens, and the Wrath of Hammerdeath will be yours.
Whew! There certainly were a lot of pirates around here.
Fight well! Show no mercy!
I've got children of my own, so I understand why my lady is trying to save her son. But it's not safe.
Take that meat to Wort. You'll find him on the road to the east of here.
The flesh of this corpse is dotted with live maggots.
The flesh of this corpse is dotted with live maggots.
The flesh of this corpse is dotted with live maggots.
Can't wait to be back on the open sea again. Alcaire is too landlocked for me.
Can't wait to be back on the open sea again. Alcaire is too landlocked for me.
Whew! There certainly were a lot of pirates around here.
Can you believe it? Thistlewhip's hunters sent down a whole clutch of thunderbug eggs!
Have you had any luck finding out who I can and can't trust on my crew?
The Imperials may have been checked in Haven, but their arrows still fly over the razorvines that protect us.
I went beyond the city's walls once.nnEven the trees had eyes!
Some say Baron Gradwyn's men were in the right, but they didn't save us from Duke Bealton, so what does it really matter?
Take my advice, stranger. nnStay near Daggerfall. Don't trust anyone from Wayrest.
During the war, there was a shortage of ale. Imagine that!nnSome taverns were charging far too much for what little they had.
Some say Baron Gradwyn's men were in the right, but they didn't save us from Duke Bealton, so what does it really matter?
Some say Baron Gradwyn's men were in the right, but they didn't save us from Duke Bealton, so what does it really matter?
Some say Baron Gradwyn's men were in the right, but they didn't save us from Duke Bealton, so what does it really matter?
I'm not familiar with the Daggerfall Covenant. nnI only know that they named it after our great city.
Living in a city is harder than being out in the country, even if it's safer from invaders.
I haven't heard from my brother in Camlorn for some time now. nnHe used to send word regularly. What do you suppose happened out there?
Now that my daughter's grown,  I miss the sound of her laughter.nnShe went to Wayrest. It's a den of heathens. May Arkay protect her.
Can't offer you a reward as such, but isn't it enough to serve your king and kingdom? You are from here, aren't you?
I'm glad to see you've returned. How did your search go?
The brazier will be just below a tower in the ruins. Be careful. There's no telling what lurks in the ruins now.
I used to own a hunting lodge near Camlorn, but I lost those lands in the last war.
I'm not used to seeing so many others here. Redguards, Dunmer, Khajiit....nnNext thing you know, they'll be letting in more Argonians!
I know you have your own agenda, but as you can see, my farm's not the safest to wander around right now. nnI need to know if my remaining farmhands are going to stay for the long haul.
The King and Queen of Daggerfall rarely appear in public these days.
You won't find any goods in Wayrest as good as the ones you'll find right here in Daggerfall.
If he's resisting, you may have no choice but to kill him. It happens.nnI'd rather see him dead than on the loose.
Our father died. Soon we'll take him to join the tribe of old King Toad-Eye in the Bonebarrow.

Don't get close. Our friend the Commander is getting... ripe. You know these Imperial soldiers. they don't bathe like real people. They're just tall pigs at heart.nnQuiet, Commander! I don't want to hear any more noise from that bag.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
I'm a strong supporter of the Julianos School.nnWe're Bretons, after all, and we need to train our children well. We shouldn't entrust their education to that upstart Mages Guild!
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
There are few Orcs in Daggerfall, but I feel comfortable wherever I go.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
The Julianos School can't possibly compare with the opportunities the Mages Guild offers.
This city has too much stone and not enough trees for my taste.
My parents still speak of Ranser's War as though it was yesterday.nnThings have been peaceful enough since then.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
Excuse me. You've interrupted my private devotions.
By the Eight! You startled this one from a daydream!
King Casimir used to walk about Daggerfall when he was younger.nnNow he's rarely seen in public.
There are very few Redguards in Glenumbra.nnThe ones who come here in times of war aren't likely to remain.
May the Eight walk beside you, stranger, wherever your path may lead.
There's enough fighting in the woods to keep my blood flowing.
There may be a need for warriors elsewhere.nnI don't know how much longer I can stay in this place.
The glorious smell of incense is all around us. Well done.nnI've finished the last of the preparations, so we may begin. nnAdding magical essence is the next step.
Ugh! I was about to bite that fool's face off! Why'd you cheat me of my victory?
Haven is lost, overrun by gods know what. I'll never go back there.
Haven is lost, overrun by gods know what. I'll never go back there.
I won't stop searching until I find Lea's body and put her soul to rest.
These people would do well to remember when Orcs ruled the land.
There are few Orcs in Daggerfall, but I feel comfortable wherever I go.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
I can't wait to leave Daggerfall. The people here are so small-minded.
This city has too much stone and not enough trees.
By the Eight, what day is it? I'm probably late for something!
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
Excuse me. You've interrupted my private devotions.
By the Eight, you startled this one from a daydream!
King Casimir used to walk about Daggerfall when he was younger. Now he's rarely seen in public.
There are few Redguards in Glenumbra The ones who come here in times of war aren't likely to remain.
May the Eight walk beside you, stranger, wherever your path leads you.
There is no point in living if you don't fight from time to time. You agree with me, right? Right?
There may be a need for warriors elsewhere. I don't know how much longer I can remain in this place.
Your soul is foul with the filth of Cold Harbor. You should rest in Arkay's light.
Sload? What's a sload? Is it good to eat?
I don't think the Imperials are building any catapults.nnThank Y'ffre. Can you imagine the number of trees they would have cut down?
The Lion Guard is here to support the Daggerfall Covenant.
I've travelled across Glenumbra several times now. nnThe Lion Guard goes wherever it's needed most.
There are few Redguards in Glenumbra. Those who come here in times of war are unlikely to remain.
This is supposed to make the vines around this camp grow? This one doesn't understand. Surely a big pile of sh- of fertilizer would be better?nnBosmer make no sense. This one is getting a headache.
We escaped from Haven with little more than the shirts on our backs.nnOr armor, as the case may be.

I'm keeping watch for Thistlewhip's return. If I can't help guard his back while he hunts, I can at least ensure his meal is warm and filling.nnDoes that sound pathetic? I hope he doesn't think so....
Daggerfall is an old city with strong roots. It has a spirit not unlike Orsinium.
I am no longer anchored to this accursed necropolis! nnThe merchant at the gates...nnTake us to her! Hide us within her caravan. We must escape!
It is a great honor to be chosen for the Knights of the Dragon.
target: It is a great honor to be chosen for the Knights del Drago.

source: By the end of my shift, I'm always ready for a flagon of ale.
The dockside's the least of our worries.nnI hear there's been real trouble over in Camlorn.
Kynareth's blessings, stranger.
Watch your step around the dockyards. nnWe're here to protect people, but we can't be everywhere at once.
I serve my city and its people with pride.
Ah, the bright and rising new star. Looks like <<1>> wants to test your metal. nnYou'll want some pine charcoal to fuel the forge. It's the black stuff.
<<1>>! it is good to see that you are still studying the craft. And to think that I thought you had no true interest. Are you ready for  your journeyman test?
Being an outfitter is rewarding, <<1>>. but I have nothing more to teach you.nnGo to Wayrest if you wish to continue your studies.

<<1>>, it is time for you to be trialed. Instead of the traditional crafting of a ring, I wish to explore your soul nnHmmm . I fear that Hastien has misplaced my soul gems. nnOh well, we shall fall back on to tradition. Are you ready?
Kynareth's blessings, stranger.
Did you find Galas? nnWhy is he not with you?
You told Nedre I was dead, right? If you didn't, then I might be dead soon... when she comes to kill me....
I assume the Foreman only confirmed what I told you.  If you were able to befriend him, the best thing to do is get in House Dres' trust and find out more.
I'll tend to the sick, the weak, and the wounded. nnSee what you can do about those cores.
Ordinator Goval is well acquainted with the flora and fauna of Stonefalls. nnIf anyone could determine if the Dreugh are infected, it's him.
Where's Reme? What did you say to her?
Where's Reme?
Did Nivele seem upset? nnYou didn't upset her, did you?nnDid you get the key for Raijo?
Ah, welcome back to our glorious Blightfence.  Any news from the House?
Hello, hello my friend.  Did you change your mind about a shirt?  Or a new cloak?  It's always such a pleasure to see you.
Necris is to the northeast of Kragenmoor.  We get many of the bones that make up the Blightfence there.
As the Ashlanders say, "revenge is best served cold." I shall wait with anticipation to see Ravnos fail over the next few months.
I cannot imagine life without her.
The nixads will carry word of your deed across all of Valenwood. The Hero of the Scarlet Summit! My hero....
Have you filled a soul cage with the spirits of the damned?
Have you had any luck recovering those remains?nnMy colleagues at the Mages Guild have sent couriers asking about the state of the expedition.nnI'd like to offer them some good news.
Hero of the Summit! Hero!
To be cursing of the Imperial invaders. The inconvenience of confinement! The foulness of the odors!
Hisssss. Chi-ree chi-ree!
To be missing Lurmpi terribly. The crowding of the strangers! The parasites ungroomed from my fur!
Hissss. Hoot hoot! Slurrrrrrrp!
You have the... ingredients? Excellent! Now, just put them in the beaker and... wait, who are you again?
I very much look forward to our meal together.
You've returned our home to us. How can we ever thank you?
You go any further, I'll break your legs.
You should talk with my sister Janand in the Guild Hall, just up the hill. May the Eight walk with you, Guild Candidate!
I'm trying to hurry, really.
When the goblins face the hatred they've visited on others, they'll have to reconsider their blind anger.
Have the Rock Biter goblins learned the error of their ways?
Both Bealton's Raiders and Gradwyn's Knights are to blame for the slaughter in Westtry. They should never have fought among innocent people.
My poor Toves  but what you did was right. nnEven if he now thinks of me with scorn, at least he will be safe.
I do not feel my love's presence here any longer... what have you done, stranger?
That is what I call commitment! I can get on board with someone like you.nnI hope the Prince doesn't need me just yet. I've got some cleaning up to do.
That Prince Aeradan... what a fellow! I wonder if he knows what I'm thinking right now?
Has that one warned the others?
All done, then?
Daggerfall is an old city with strong roots. It has a spirit not unlike Orsinium.
You've done good this day.
Another show will be starting soon. nnIn the meantime, why not enjoy some lady fingers from our concession tent? They're simply to die for!

You dear, kind soul, healing my Senche out of the kindness of your heart. A thousand thanks to you!nnNow. About that Prince. I know what he wants. If he seeks to drive the Imperials out from our wood, then I am with him. I give my word.

Follow this road west. When you see the barricade, look for my brother, <<1>>. He'll get you past the Imperials.nnThe Dominion forces move too slowly. They want to wait and organize while the noose draws tight around my people's throats!
You have my word, <<1>>. All that I know, so shall the Queen and her Thalmor know. There was never a truer soul than Excellent Ervas.
I could smell the burning cargo from here. Well done.
We've spread word of your deeds under sun and sky. nnConsider yourself welcome in the village of the Kagesh.

Do not be so surprised by my concern. nnI enjoy my work here. It brings me great pride. I also enjoy my head staying attached to my shoulders and avoiding any wild magics that the Ashlanders spew out in order to continue my... business.
Salvage? I won't give them the satisfaction. I'd spit in their faces if they offered me a drink on my deathbed.
You found the grave? Then what are you doing back here? nnWhat do you think that shovel is for?
I accounted for almost every situation possible to ensure my daughter inherits my fortune.nnI never would have thought it possible that Necris would fall under the shadow of necromancy.
Long ago, Runk put Mudgum in fur. Itchy and sticky, but Runk catch many bugs, so was good.
The liberation of Brump! nnThe confounding of the Imperials!
We're not afraid to die in battle. We do what we must.
I heard you escorted one of ours safely to Davon's Watch.nnI also heard he went straight into quarantine. I think I'll take my chances right here.
<<1>> has bones?
That worthless s'wit...nnOh, you're back, my friend!
You made it back fast.
We must enter the rift between past and present. Head up, out of my tomb, and step through it.
You've had your revenge. I'm doomed to die, but you'll have to kill many others to stop my plague.

Desperation turns our citizens to vice. The ordinators do nothing except but punish them for it.nnI've implored the Houses to reach out to their residents, but they're too busy squabbling to pay me any mind.
Across the water to the north is where you'll find the Orc camp. Go insult the Orc Chieftan.
Run back to your masters, Imperial dog...
Whatever happened inside that temple, we can rest assured the ritual has been disrupted. All the wood's inhabitants are in your debt.
Dear gods, will you get me out of here?
Senie has seen enough strife - do not add to their woes.
So many sick, and we sit powerless... please let the Diviner know what has occured.
Meep meep meep!
My sister is out there, somewhere. She would not have told you to find me if she did not want to be found.nnPerhaps I can find some way to lift her curse.
You found the key? Excellent. The jewelry box must be in that same building somewhere.
Ah, friend, thank you for helping Ferema!nnShe planted a kiss upon my cheek, in public, no less! I will certainly be the butt of jests for some time to come!
Why have they not released me yet? Has Jivon abandoned me here?
You have my deepest thanks. I don't know what I would have done without my belongings.
Where is the tongue?  Tell me you found him and spilt his blood over the ground!
Come back here when you can't find any more ghosts to fight. We need to have a talk.
Lady Elise is your focus, but all of the survivors in Camlorn are depending on you to find them.
Get a drop of the purple potion, a pinch of reagent and then combine them with the bergamont seeds in the alchemy set.
It is right and just that the merchants deal only with House Dres.  Also most lucrative.  How did you fare?
Who gave you leave to enter my tent, unworthy one?
House Dres loyal, that's my new pledge.  I buy only from them.  So should we all.
I meant what I said.  You're no longer welcome here.  Do your business and get out.
If we are to support House Dres, then that's what I suppose we will do.  Long live House Dres...
You saved us from a fate worse than dying.
You saved us from a fate worse than dying.
You saved us from a fate worse than dying.
You saved us from a fate worse than dying.
You saved us from a fate worse than dying.
Excellent work, especially for a novice herder!
If we can survive this Blight long enough, perhaps the Three will have mercy on us. If not, at least we will be together again.
Take the Life Timber Seeds and plant them in the Blighted Gnarls and the Pestilent Root within Black Log to the east.
Thank you for the snake meat. Without your help, we would have been stuck out here with no food.
My master sent me to collect the secret ingredient to his fabled sujamma, but what he neglected to tell me was the kwama I'm to get it from are quite vicious!
Lifetimber will rise again thanks to you!
I serve my city and my people with pride.
Have you seen these prices? These merchants are all trying to reduce us to poverty!
During the war, there was a shortage of ale. Imagine that! nnSome taverns were charging far too much for what little they had.
Living in a city is harder than living out in the country, even though it's safer from invaders.
Working as an apprentice in Wayrest much more interesting than starving as a farmer in Gavaudon.
Don't talk to me about the Daggerfall Covenant. What a terrible name for something so important! nnThey should have called it the Wayrest Covenant. That's a lot more dignified.
Wars keep the lower classes occupied and generally out of mischief.
I'm not interested in politics. The subject bores me. nnWhy can't we talk about something else?
I don't mind saying that sometimes I long for the old days.nnStill, they say we're better off now than ever before.
When I was young, I travelled with my parents to Daggerfall once.nnI can assure you, it's nothing compared to Wayrest's grandeur.
We're too far from the mountains here, but at least they're visible in the distance.
My family and I will leave as soon as we can arrange safe passage elsewhere.
This city has too much stone and not enough trees for my taste.
My parents still speak of Ranser's War as though it happened yesterday. nnI don't see why. Life has been peaceful enough since then.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
Wayrest is amusing, but I cannot wait to return to Vvardenfell.
By the Eight! You startled this one from a daydream!
The merchants of Wayrest charge too much for basic necessities. It's scandalous!
Wayrest is the only home I've ever known.
May the Eight walk beside you, stranger, wherever your path may lead you.
There's enough fighting in the wilds nearby to keep my blood flowing.
There may be a need for warriors elsewhere. nnI don't know how much longer I will remain in this place.
These people would do well to remember when Orcs ruled the land.
There's plenty of work for skilled artisans like me here in Wayrest.
I have no interest in whatever you may be peddling, stranger.
Wayrest is filled with so many small-minded people.
Stormhaven's rains are legendary. nnSince ancient days, the storms have washed away entire mountains!
You should rest, traveller. You seem tired.
I'm not interested in whatever you're peddling, stranger.
Excuse me. You have interrupted my private devotions.
By Alkosh's Whiskers! You startled this one from a daydream!
This one has only been to Elsweyr in dreams.
There aren't many Redguards in High Rock. nnAny Redguard who comes here in a time of war isn't likely to stay.
May the Eight walk beside you, stranger, wherever your path may lead you.
There is no point in living if you don't start a few fights from time to time, wouldn't you say?
There may be a need for warriors elsewhere. nnI don't know how much longer I can stay here.
Arkay bless you, <<1>>. Be wary of undead wolves and bandits. Both threaten heroes who would serve the Divines.
You have a familiar smell about you, one that makes Kal-J'rei's stomach rumble.
That poor mammoth trampled out long deserved justice.
Hello again, friend. I'm afraid I've gotten no better since we last talked. But I must stay strong for Iena...
Don't worry about me anymore. There are plenty of other needy souls out in the world.
That's an interesting coin you have.nnRa'Gadan, if I'm not mistaken. nnYou don't see many of those in Morrowind.
You don't look like a Bloodthorn cultist. I assume this is a rescue attempt?
The Lion Guardr is here to support the Daggerfall Covenant.
I'm fine. Hic! What's your problem?
Use the path that leads north to the Siege Camp. I'm sure you'll find plenty of corrupted beasts to slay on the way there.
This one is pleased to meet a friend of Marthe Rielle. Ahji could use your aid in finding the Werereaver.
Not long ago, Orcs ruled much of this land. I'm proud of my heritage.
Maybe someday I'll travel to Hammerfell. nnUnder the Daggerfall Covenant, we're allowed to live wherever we please. I plan to take advantage of that.
By Alkosh's whiskers! You startled this one from a daydream!
This one has never been to Elsweyr, save in dreams.
You'll find many supporters of the Daggerfall Covenant in Wayrest. nnBeyond the city is another matter entirely...
Without the Redguards, the Daggerfall Covenant has no teeth.
The Dominion has strengthened Valenwood, Summerset, and Elsweyr. Some Bosmer ignore the treaty and hold old grudges.
You look like you've found something, friend. What troubles you?
It is done? <<1>>? nnDid you... end him?
You were wise not to turn against us. nnMy blade would of been buried in your flesh the moment you did.
Please wait for me outside. I'll only be a moment.
The Lion Guard is here to support the Daggerfall Covenant and ensure peace throughout Stormhaven.
We're not interested in the local politics, though rumors say otherwise.
May the Eight bless you, traveller.
The Dwemer may be long dead, but their machinations still torment us to this day.
Ah, you have the gems.  Now use them on my trapped guides, and their souls will be free.
I hate being this weak. I hate it!
I could pass out from euphoria. One of the eggs just hatched in my mouth!
The water-seeker returns. Any success?
I'll rest here for now. I'm certain Father Montague and those he protected are grateful.
I'll rest here for now. I'm certain Father Montague and those he protected are grateful.
I'll rest here for now. I'm certain Father Montague and those he protected are grateful.
You have my thanks... and the eternal gratitude of my ancestors.
Be wary of looters. nnIf we weren't stretched so thin between this disease and the disaster at Senie, we'd have taken care of them a long time ago.
Are those my gems, weighing down your pack?  Excellent!
I'm glad to see you return - if you took much longer Fadron and I would have had to go looking for your poison-bloated body among the pools.  nnI jest, I jest.  What have you brought me?
Is it time to eat yet?  The miners are not the only ones who are hungry
target: Qa-dur's stomach is growling like Ahnurr himself.

source: Did you find the mazte? nnIf I don't get some soon, I might fall asleep... again!
Just get close to the netchlings, and give 'em a poke with the stick I gave you. They're docile enough after that.nnBetty Netch don't take kindly to disturbing their young, so you need to be quick.
From your expression, I can tell that you've seen something strange.nnHave you found the source of the tarn's corruption?
Do you truly wish to save me? To save all of our souls? Perhaps... hope is not yet lost.
Glad to see you made it out of there, my friend.  Better luck than any of us have had, that's for certain.
These sacks you carry are promising.  Did you get the tools?
Did you return the treasure? I don't want to die to the curse!
Were you able to get your hands on the discs?
Have something to prove, stranger? nnWould you have me think you do this out of the goodness of your heart?nnYou perplex me.
I saw a scarlet flame in you when you first approached. We would do well to have one such as you in our tribe.
I worry what the Wise Woman would do if she saw me invoking the ancestors despite her admonitions. I do not wish to get in an altercation.
Oh, you've done it!nnPlease, let me see the spider part. Please!nnI am... pleased.
Your arms are full - this is a good sign.  You must have done well in your task!
Is that Slouchbear Steak I smell? Oh yes!nnLet me tell you, it's hungry work jumping around in these trees all day. Thanks, friend.
If you wish to aid us, go to Senie and seek out Giras.nnHouse Cousin Giras' resources are taxed to the limit. If I could send more aid to him, I would have already.
I have no treatment for these poor ailing souls. nnMy egg-mother used to make this salve for us when we were sick with fever.nnIt served us well.
Are you looking to assist in the war effort?
Is it done? Is Andre's last wish fulfilled?
Thank Akatosh there's someone willing to do something about these cretins.
That's all I stole, <<1>>. I'm poor now. Again.
Thank you so much for going to Sibellec's swamp for me.nnI hope the journey wasn't too dangerous.
If anyone asks, we never spoke.
If we take the guards' weapons, not only will we be dangerous, but the guards will no longer be a threat. What use is a guard with no weapon to fight with?
<<1>> and Vusara were both promising in their potential. nnIt's a shame to see them disregard what they've pledged to uphold.

If we had brought more of the seasoned warriors with us this would be no problem. Unfortunately you don't get pleasant results when you throw a handful of relic seekers with knowledge of the old world and not of combat into the mix.
The Dousing Tonic will not destroy the flamed ones, only weaken them slightly. You'll need to count on your wits and strength in order to truly defeat them.
I think I will sleep now, commander.nnThank you so much for coming personally to relive me from my post. It is good to know that Daggerfall has not forgotten its loyal soldiers.
Animals were drawn to the center and began attacking each other, did they not?nnLuckily the scroll only allows a moment of perception. You did not witness them ingest each other and become the Hunt.
The Blacksaps came out of nowhere. I had to leave everything behind.
Have you found them yet? They shouldn't be hard to get from their owners... they're basically animals, you know.
<<1>>'s beastly brothers infest our town like a fungus. Search them out and put an end to their brutish, hedonist lives.
Such a tragedy. They've degenerated into mindless beasts. nnPerhaps one day we'll be able to cure them, but today is not that day.
A part of me died in the place, friend. nnI am weary.
My home, far to the east, was overrun by savage Blacksaps. I came here to convince the Dominion to save us, but it seems they're too busy trying to save Leaftower.
So many dead. What do we have to do with kings and queens? Why did they do this to us?
They say the Blacksaps march their prisoners up to the dead town of Gil-Var-Delle.
I was awake when the Blacksap attacked. I managed to wake up a few of my neighbors.
Our fortunes will turn any day now, friend <<1>>.
And how was your time on Valmori's bent stick on the water he dares to call a boat?
How did you fare among the unwell?

I fear the addict you speak of is an old friend. nnSkooma ruined our relationship. I did my best to help him, but to no avail.nnNow I know more about skooma than I'd ever wish to know, but not many are aware of this... except for him.

The mad thing, our "Treethane," stalks the woods, to south and east, alone. Can you track him? Do you know how to find his trail? If not, no fear. His hunting camp is due east. Sooner, or later, the monster returns there.
Those lying charlatans are everywhere around this city.  nnGo! Exact my vengeance!
I don't know what I'd do without Sugar...
How did it taste?
We can't fall asleep. It's too dangerous.
Even in armor with a weapon, I'd be useless in battle. Y'ffre sent you to rescue us and for this I am glad.
Most excellent. Now to burn them in the sacred braziers! nnThere are five posted in the immediate temple area. There's one for each heart.
Have you found the secret message yet?
In time Gil-Var-Delle will return to Valenwood, starting with Black Log.

Many survivors in Crosswych can't face the risen miners. After all, we're a mining community, and the undead miners are people we know.nnExcuse me. I should have said the undead were "people we knew."
Once, I believed in the Tribunal's power. No more.nnWith all this suffering around me, how can I think they care a whit about our fate?

The relics that rest within will surely be tainted with Daedric magic. Use great care in handling these items. It's entirely possible that the magic within them could very well shift upon the one who holds it, cursing them for all eternity.

Were they fierce? Were they ferocious? nnI bet my little mechanical critters had those big goofy Ogrim running in circles in fear! I enchanted each of them with a magical ward that inspires terror when near!nnWait... what happened?
With that stone, you might just be able to defeat the Huntress.
Oh Briran, did you think me a fool? I am always the one to have the last laugh!

If you killed him, you'd attract the attention of the guards.nnA little blow to the head won't hurt him much. It wouldn't cause as much alarm as a dead body would.nnHe usually patrols the road leading to the keep's bridge. It's a nice secluded spot.
Galvo, we can't leave our son! nn<<1>>, you have to go back!nnWhat if our son dies while we're gone? I couldn't live with myself if that happened.
Have you seen my son? nnWe can't wait much longer for him, but I'm loathe to travel back to the fort. nnOur departure was not without controversy.
Ah, he's about to strike, I know it! Look at him, pretending he doesn't know what I'm talking about!
What's this? That glimmer... the Silvenar! Yes!nnThe Silvenar is inside you. I am confident of it this time.
The Huntress has something to fear in you - Goreclaw was one of her lieutenants!
Kwama like to hide under spongy mushrooms and shale fragments. nnThey're very particular about their foraging grounds.
I have no wish to harm them. Returning what is rightfully ours is my only concern.
I'm thinking of buying some of those remedies, but I haven't heard anything good about them. Then again, what harm could it do?
I'm thinking of buying some of those blight remedies, but I haven't heard anything good about them. But what harm could it do?
By the Three, that's the most disgusting scent my nose has ever come across. Even my own men have returned to the temple for fear of turning sick.
You're bold, for meat. What do you want?
It's quieter here already.nnI think you've had some success.
Someone has been making our noble house look ignoble.nnIt's my responsibility to fix that.
Did you find any of my things?nnIs anyone awake in there?
Hurry, please. They must be bewitched by the spirits that roam these ruins! It's the only explanation! Go, before it's too late for both of them!
Hurry, please. They must be bewitched by the spirits that roam these ruins! It's the only explanation! Go, before it's too late for both of them!
May the Divines bless your path, <<1>>.nnThank you. My family and I will never forget what you've done for us.
Tell me you were successful.nnI can feel a change in the very air around us.
The swamp feels so cold without her near.

I do apologize for my rudeness in asking you to fight for me. I assure you, were the need not dire I would be a more appropriate host. I promise you, when all of this is over we will make you as welcome as you so richly deserve.
You've saved us out here. Lord Gemin will be very happy to hear about this.
Thank you for checking on Blanche. Let's keep her location between us, shall we?
I hope you brought weapons.
Once you've finished with your Imperial bloodbath, come back. I'll have something ready for you by then.
I'll be keeping an eye out for anything that might stop you.nnAnd of course, I'll be watching you. Can you blame me?
Stay alert, citizen.
The palate suddenly becoming dry.nnThe eyes widening to express yearning.nnThe mouth salivating at the thought of delicious amberberries!
You did it?
Deserving to be Cliffvoot Sentry!nnWatching Elder Brump resting.nnProud to be so kind to Elder Brump!
Knowing the <<1>> was talking to Yoon! nnWanting to talk to Yoon....nnTalking with punches and kicks!
The <<1>> was talking to Yoon! Shoof is wanting to talk to Yoon too. nnTalk with smacks and kicks!
Protecting Cliffvoot! nnBeing a hero!nnThe calm exhalation of a long breath. nnThe relaxed ease at the end of a long day.

Seeing the Night Stone fall from the sky. Watching it land near the waterfall.nnWill the <<1>> be using the Night Stone for sentry rites?nnWatching two apparitions of threats of Valenwood. nnWill the <<1>> be defeating them?
I assume you've heard that Martin enlisted in the Shornhelm Guard. I'm glad, but I do worry for his safety. I hope he enlisted for the right reasons.

Seeing the Night Stone fall from the sky many moons ago. Landing there, next to the waterfall.nnThe <<1>> will be using the Night Stone for sentry rites. It will be creating two apparitions; the threats of Valenwood. The <<1>> must be defeating them.
We lost today. Thanks to you, some survived to fight again tomorrow.
Will the <<1>> be entering the Tiger Tunnels?nnWill the valiant hero be fecthing Baf's satchel from his broken wagon?
Thank you for tracking down my partner. It wouldn't be the same without that scaly lizard around.
Oh, poor <<1>>! Unkind fate! nnThis was her first voyage to the mainland. Now she is lost beyond her wits.nnPerhaps you should begin searching for her. May I suggest... immediately?
Have you brought the painting of Lady Sofia?
The frolicsome sway upon a scenic perch. The delightful crunch of a favorite treat. The momentary rest for an intreped <<1>>.
Dark. Cold. Dry. Worse than death this prison is. But my bindings cannot be broken like a dead branch. nnThere is no escape, no release.
You've defeated the evil in Camlorn!nnI wish I could have been by your side in that fight. nnThe bards will sing of your victory for ages.
Do you have my shovel?nnI've been waiting to get my hands on it for ages!
They sought to control Grahtwood!
Use the stone I gave you to calm aggressive spriggans.
Watch yourself out there. We've lost too many good soldiers already.
Thank you. I don't know how you found me, but I'm glad you did.
Yes. Take the insignia and cast them into his fire. I hope the smoke chokes his accursed breath!
You get used to the mosquitos.
You get used to the mosquitos.
Well done, young one.
Mud keeps the mosquitos off your skin.nnNo one here will be impressed by how clean you are. nnBe practical!
Is that my Leia I hear?
You've done well, stranger. nnYou're welcome to stay in Mireblossom as long as you like.nnConsider yourself a member of the tribe!
She has heard their cries from here. It is the sweetest of sounds. nnHave you killed her children, <<1>>?
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
One day, <<1>>, I'll tell my children I met you at the battle for Camlorn.
One day, <<1>>, I'll tell my children I met you at the battle for Camlorn.
One day, <<1>>, I'll tell my children I met you at the battle for Camlorn.
One day, <<1>>, I'll tell my children I met you at the battle for Camlorn.
Good hunting, <<1>>. If I survive this battle, maybe you can tell me where you came from.
I'll not drink.nnCan't kill wolves this way. Gaelle... Gaelle must be ashamed of me.
You'll be able to get pelts from the lowland wolves just outside.nnPlease be careful. I saw some larger wolves out there as well.
Oh! You startled me. I'm searching for my sister Jayne. Thankfully, this wasn't her.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
Have you seen my family? I know they were here before I got sick.
I'll rest here a moment and then make my way outside.
Any luck finding my pickaxe? My father gave it to me, and I can't go back to work without it.
Our foals are scattered. Most of them ran northwest of our village.nnPlease find them before anything happens to them.
Thank you again for saving me. If you had not show up I believe I would have been transformed into one of those horrid monsters in the cave.
Did you manage to gather all my bottles of Crosswych Ale. Did you crack open those little mucky little claw monsters?
You saved me... I never met anyone in these woods who was friendly to Imperials.

Did you find any good sinew for my bow? I need musculature that's resiliant and pliable.nnI really should have brought some with me... or at least practiced my proficiency with a blade. Live and learn!
Do you really think you'll be able to get past that huge spider?
Each passing generation strengthens my bond with my children and my people.nnThe foals and children grow together as one, and I will protect them with every fiber of my being.
Raoul said he was going further into the mine. I hope he's all right.
I could hear Isaura calling for help earlier
target: she can't be too far away.

source: Isaura is a strong woman. My guess is that she made it further into the mine than Piers. Perhaps into the Central Tunnel, even.
Well this is a surprise. Hello!
If we can get the mine open again, it'll be good for everyone.nnI hope those support beams will hold. If they fail, I'm not sure the mine will ever be safe again, even after we clear out the undead.
You've found all the <<1>> we need! nnBring it to <<2>> to the east of Merovec's Folly. He can use the ore to enchant our weapons.
Will the <<1>> be opening this cage to free Elder Brump?
Tell me what you saw! I must know!
I can't thank you enough for rescuing my wife. I couldn't live without her.
You've made it back alive. Glad to see you're still in one piece.
Did you recover my supplies from those horrible highwaymen?
Have you found my betrothed?
Now all we need to do is mend the wagons and we could be in Northpoint by nightfall.
There's a lot of fish in that river to the east.  One of them might have eaten Gustave's ring by now.
The bone colossus roams along the outer wall of Cath Bedraud and these tombs. I would be wary. Don't tackle it alone.

If I didn't already think Marcenya was daft for wanting to visit those cursed ruins, I'd be convinced now. She wants to sneak through the Imperial lines and then visit the ruins.nnY'ffre, what fools these Altmer be.
You're right about me. I'm a no-good thief.
This is disastrous! My manor! Utterly destroyed. These monsters have ruined everything.
Have you seen any of the Razorvine hunters here in the Refuge? Me neither.
You tore my body apart! I felt it! I'm free!
<The spirit bows its head to you in thanks.>
Ah! Look, my dear, it's the brave adventurer I asked to find you. I'm so sorry for your trouble - my daughter has made her own way home! Why don't you introduce yourself, <<1>>?
Please believe me... I have no harmful intentions here. I only wish to live among them in peace, and know the warmth of a loving parent.
You look like you could use a drink. I have just the thing.
I don't have time for idle chatter, I'm afraid. What little time I have left, I hope to spend spitting on an Orc's mutilated corpse.
Chopped off any Daedra heads yet?nnI swear, every time I turn around, there are more of those things.
Be on your guard. We don't know what you'll face after you enter the ruins. nnJust find their altars and do what you need to do. Get in and get out!
Thanks for saving me!  I'll show you to a secret passage.
The Protector of the Grove chose well in soliciting your help on behalf of Elden Grove,  <<1>>. You are both a wise and powerful adventurer.
I'm almost certain the incantation is "Arkay's Beard," but Akatosh is a more reliable deity.nnIt's definitely one of those two. I think.
What can I do for you?

The other day one of the Colovian refugees asked if I could loan him a coin. I asked why. He said he wanted to bribe the guards to let him have more food.nnAfter I told him I respected his honesty, I kicked him right down the ramp.

Thanks again for your help! nnNow that I'm feeling better, I can bake more! That is, if I can get Loane to show me where she put the flour.nnAfter she learned I used it to bake the first cake, she hid it away.
I don't recognize you, which makes me think I shouldn't be talking to you. Good day.
This used to be such a care-free place. Now, it's a military camp. Literally!
Thanks to you, I'm sure to be safe if the undead make it to Northpoint.
Without the blessings of the Watchers, my herds will starve this coming winter.
I cannot even think straight with that foul corruption near me. Please, destroy it!
Go on about your business, <<1>>. I've got more important things to do than chat with you. This place isn't going to guard itself.
It warms my heart to see all that stuff burning. nnYou should be able to get in that cave now to free the rest of the crew. Go for it! I'll be waiting up here to cover their escape.
Oh <<1>>, <<1>>. Why can't you see we were meant for each other?
I refuse to even speak with that foolish girl. You had better tell her for me - if she insists on maintaining this charade, there will be repercussions. Serious repercussions!
You found my sextant! Wonderful! nnPlease take it to my father. He lives in Farmost Reach, southwest of here.nnHe may be glad to finally know what happened to me.

Through the trials we face, we learn from our choices. nnWe never give up, even when we fail. We take responsibility and do what we must. nnWe sacrifice our wants and needs for the benefit of those around us.
If you have not done so, seek out the Trial of the Mind.nnIf all the tasks before you are complete, speak to Verandis near his table.
There's nothing left of me. I gave it all to her.
Ah, back for more, are we? nnI would love to stay with you for a while longer, but I must return to my duties.nnDon't forget me.
Knarstygg told me what you have done for Murk-Watcher. nnThough this seems dangerously unnatural to Dro-Dara, there is no point in questioning it now.
Ever since you freed us, Murk-Watcher has been sitting out there, just staring at those crocodiles.nnIt's strange. They've been leaving her alone.  Maybe she's worked some of her old charms on them.
We  we failed  and no one will know.

Many farmhands drowned when the levees were broken. Others were eaten by the crocodiles.nnIt's not the beasts' fault, though. It is their nature to hunt. Their spirits sing a song my heart hears. It is the song of the crocodile.
It's true. There are many brawls in the Cat Box. nnThat just proves the quality of our liquor, eh?
I don't know you. What do you want?
I desire no more of your watered-down liquor.
I can barely hear over those damned drunks.
I'lllll take you home again, Solihaaaa.nThrough the treeees so dim and greeeen.nAnd bear you up upoooon the bouuuughs.nAnd show you then my great big- urp!nnUgh. Excuse me. Need to- urp!
What a fight! Shanari sure is wily, isn't she? nnThat's the advantage of living long and well!
This Blackmaul mercenary is dead.
l'll walk with a limp for the rest of my life, won't I?
Any luck healing the injured scout or finding the stolen pack?
That did not work out very well. You have to be quicker next time!nnWhat do you think? Should we try it once more?
I am eager to return to Summerset.
Recapturing Southpoint was yet another victory for the Dominion. Praise Queen Ayarynne!
Did you get everything? The blossoms, the mudcrab claws? Did you forget the wine?
Auri-El guide my blade!
Ithguleoir is dead? I can hardly believe it! nnHenri can finally start fishing again. He certainly can't use Ithguleoir as an excuse anymore!
Imperials! Daedric cults! This just gets worse and worse.nnIs there anything else we should be finding in Blacksap Village? nnIf you find something worse, by all means, let me know.
You smell of ogre blood and victory, friend. You have the teeth?
<<1>> thanks you for finding her sister.nnHowever, this one still wonders why the Blackmauls don't take away Bretons, Orcs, or Redguards.
Find one of the soldiers we sent to examine the cave. Maybe they figured out a way to close the tunnel.
The Blood Thorn must suffer for their crimes.
Were you able to find any wildflowers? nnI detect the familiar scent of their fragrance about you.
I'm still swamped with wounded conscripts. They're only good for two things: bleeding and dying.n nGive me some good news. Did you collect any chains from the dead? That would be great.
He tried to order me to return to the camp.nnFoolish man. As if I'd leave him now!
You can't feel what I'm feeling, can you?nnSomething beyond this door is singing in my veins. I can feel it in my tainted blood.
I'm glad to see you walking back instead of floating. Did you have some success?
You've shown great courage and kindness. My sister and I thank you.
You're back! Were you successful?
Weerhat's pages were all scattered in the water when the nereid attacked. nnBy now, the tide will have caried them north of here. Thankfully, vellum does not rot easily.

I sent Crelie to Farwatch after you left. Something is amiss here - these ruins are centuries old, yet something still powers them. Now that I've felt the suffering of those trapped souls, I cannot turn back.nnThere must be a way past this door!
I see by your face it's not good news...
I'm certain Ineri Hlaras will have answers.
Please. You have to finish it. We were so close! nnJust those last three support beams and we'd have caved it in. Boom. No more ogres.
If you light the ogre totems, the ogres will get angry. They might get angrier, but they'll still attack one-by-one nn unless they don't. It isn't easy to predict what ogres do.
I feel sorry for all those people who lost loved ones.nnPeople never see death coming, do they?
Jacques said that even though I'm his apprentice, I cannot be buried in the cemetery because I am Nord.nnI've lived in Gavaudon all my life! What's gotten into him?
You should get the design sheet in the house to the left. Find out what the Infernal Device is designed to do.
Go on. Destroy the Daedric idols around the Bonebarrow.nnYou've got a better chance of succeeding than I do!
The <<1>> is wanting to travel east. nnTravelling to the ruins! nnDiscovering a secret!
Who let you in? If you've come to kill me, turn around. Go back to the hole you crawled out of and tell your master Seagrave Titanborn is laughing. Go on!

You've got to help me! I mean  us. I mean the whole town!nnThe countess has gone crazy, and everyone's fighting about who should be in charge. She's the only one who can run this place. We need to help her.
If you jumped down and started fighting like mad, how many you think you'd take out before they beat you into mud?
Thanks for taking care of the Saproots for us. We've got a knack for turning the plants against our enemies.
By the by, I feel compelled to warn you that the Spriggarum has not exactly been tested yet....
Look at you! I can tell by the look of you, you're traveling around, meeting people, seeing new places.nnThat's the life I'm going back to. This plantation is doomed, and my days here are done.
Although you've brought me terrible news, you've also brought me a measure of solace.nnNow I know my wife is no longer suffering.
Thank you, stranger.nnI can't thank you and Alleim enough.
You've done the Stranded Lurk a great favor.
Did you get those reports yet?
Speak to <<1>>. He is to the north, across the plank bridge, at the edge of Imperial held territory.
It's a relief to see you again... and what's this? Do you have what I requested?
Please leave me alone. I have nothing to say to you.
Your contribution to the war effort has not gone unmarked, <<1>>. Should you find yourself in Elden Root, I recommend you visit the Thalmor.
By Vivec's Left... you certainly weren't shy with that musk! nnYou reek enough to bring a zombie to tears!

The curates deserve a proper interment, but with the Vereansu pressing their advantage, I doubt I could arrange a proper burial.nnWith things as they are, I won't be able to purchase passage to Necris for their remains.
I persevered so I could die a free soul. nnTell me... has the insignia been destroyed?
Ah, my friend! You've returned just in time... I feel my breath leaving me....
A Vereansu legend? nnDalo has spoken of such things, but only in his sleep. nnI fear he may not wake from whatever dream is consuming him.
This abomination must be destroyed, before its corruption is unleased on all of Deshaan!
I called my father down here after you went into the mine. So what happened? Did you find Beltis?
The blood on your hands tells me you were successful, my friend.
You've done me a great kindness. nnI hope good fortune follows you on your travels.
It's dangerous for you here! Leave before the guards see you!
Watch out for the guards!
Watch out, friend. The guards won't take kindly to your rescue attempt.
We're in your debt. nnHopefully, House Hlaalu will launch an investigation.nnMaybe soon, we'll be able to find the most of the afflicted the Ashlanders have smuggled through.
Thanks to you, the investigation is underway. nnYou're certainly always welcome in Narsis.
You have news for me?
My lady has heard tale of your deeds, <<1>>. nnHave you a moment?
Have you seen Falena? nnPray, tell me! What did you do?
The monument is to the west of my house, just outside of Narsis. We've met there many times on our way out of the city, to be together.nnPlease be careful. Savard doesn't know his own strength.

Start by talking to the merchants around here. They might know something. nnI suspect they'll be reticent to speak of it, though.nnI also think you should search the warehouse and the inn for anything suspicious.
Please, don't hurt me! nnWhat... what does Dirani want?
I brought my army here as a favor to King Emeric, but Murtag Clan has other battles to fight. We need to finish the Ironhand Ogres and finish them fast.nnMay your kills be quick and many, soldier.
The Vereansu are cruel. What could they possibly want with us?

Excellent work! Your timing couldn't have been better. nnAs soon as the rocks fell and crushed their Farseer, we attacked. The Vereansu were too shocked and disoriented to know what hit 'em.nnOne thing distrubs me, though....
Have you come to rescue us?
Friend, I'm not sure what you're doing, snooping about my house. I'd like to know why.nnBy the way, have you found my Ranae?
His wife will stop at nothing to destroy our love. nnNethryn is too scared to leave her! The fool!nnI know he's unhappy. This is precisely what he'd want.
Pardon me. I don't feel quite right. nnPerhaps I should take a short respite. nnI do hope it isn't something serious.
<<1>>, you've saved my life... twice.nnI chose my guards for their loyalty, but even they were seduced by this "Seeker."
I can tell by the look on your face that my suspicions were correct! What heinous goods have you discovered?
Those zombies sure make me nervous.  Please take care of them.
Thank you for reuniting me with my father.
Denying Wud's enjoyment of victory.nnHiding lighting ants!nnLaughing when Hoom discovers them!
The courage of the victor! The well-deserved congratulations.
Do my brothers and sisters walk again?
General Godrun has commandered the house at the south end of the camp.nnThere's plenty of work to go around. That's for sure.
I have seen my sister's last days. nnI have fought beside her. nnThank you.
A Daedra heart! Who would have imagined it? nnThe heart of an arcane abomination has enough magical power to alter the landscape!nnStrange, but true.

I've given you a set of traps. They should help while you're navigating through the swarm of scamps out there. nnBe careful, though! If you're careless, you'll blow your leg right off.nnI'll make preparations for moving the wounded.
By the heavens, what did you do to get them so angry? I've never seen so many Ogrim in my life. nnLots of rocks and lots of Ogrim. We'll need to act quickly. nnMaybe this will work to our advantage.

Whatever shall I do with these skins? What shall I do?nnPerhaps a line of clothing? I know! Scamp skirts! nnJust think about it. You can almost hear the sound of coins clinking in my purse! That's the sound of profit, my friend.
I'm so relieved you found my pack. nnJust the thought of facing my father's disappointment was almost enough to outweigh my fear. nnThanks for taking care of this.
I... I didn't really want the Obelus to set everybody on fire....nnThat... wow.
Please, take my sword to Princess Mira at her crypt.nnI pray she forgives me. I cannot rest until she does.
Thank you for your kind efforts, <<1>>. I am forever grateful.
Thistlewhip's hunters asked me if I wanted to eat one of the bugs they killed. But how could I be sure that the one they served isn't - that it didn't...nnI can't. I won't. I'd rather starve.
Now that the sick have been freed. We need to attend to the pass itself.

I worry about what's going on here. nnWood Orcs are not usually this aggressive, especially not this close to Elden Root. I hope they aren't planning anything, although it's hard to imagine. nnAt least life at the Trading Post is calmer... for now.
It's good to finally be rid of those restraints.
By the heavens, what did you do to get them so angry? I've never seen so many Ogrim in my life. nnLots of rocks and lots of Ogrim. We'll need to act quickly. nnMaybe this will work to our advantage.
By the heavens, what did you do to get them so angry? I've never seen so many Ogrim in my life. nnLots of rocks and lots of Ogrim. We'll need to act quickly. nnMaybe this will work to our advantage.
You are far from home, foreigner. nnWhat is your intent here? Have you crossed the seas to put an end to the Maruhkites? We have survived opponents far greater than you.
I'm impressed. Verandis was right about you, yet again. nnThat man has an uncanny way of sensing things.
If you haven't done so, seek out the Trial of the Mind.nnIf all the tasks before you are complete, speak to Verandis near his table.
You've completed all the trials set before you.nnVerandis would like to speak with you. He's waiting near a portal that will take you back to the hideout.
Please speak to my father's shade in the catacombs. nnIf he can reconcile with Mira, perhaps they can both rest.

Please don't let Verandis know about this. He'd be outraged if he knew I was dabbling in the arts of dark magic. nnOh, and if you forget where the items come from, check the list!nnYou're doing this in the name of love. Remember that!
While you're under the spell's influence, you'll walk the line between dreams and reality.nnI'll watch over your body after you've fallen asleep.
I do not know this Sleepless Dreamer, but his influence seeks to destroy all that we hold dear. nnWe must fight against him whenever we find his plans in motion.
You have done what no mortal man has done: entered Cold Harbor and returned alive.
Look down on me, and you tempt fate. nnDisease does not discriminate. nnOff to Dirdren with you.
Did you get all those reports yet?
I managed to escape with some relics, so there are only a few left. nnIf you can recover them, and look for the Warden who was captured, you'll be answering my prayers.

I can't thank you enough. nnPlease, come visit us when you can. Though the pain I feel for Verandis' loss is great, we have to continue our fight. Rivenspire isn't the only place that's in danger.nnMay the Divines watch over you, my friend.
Thank you for finding me. You were right, and I am forever in your debt.

I can't say it's not dangerous in there, but look at us! nnWe dig up things in caves. We don't go swinging swords around. We need heroes like you for that!nnHouse Hlaalu will soon be aware of your help, my friend.
I hope you were able to stop the Rock Biter's poison from reaching the people of Aldcroft. It would afflict them as it has afflicted us.
At last! We can return to Wayrest!nnWe should get Adelphe to a safe place. Then he can count those damned Soul Gems in peace.nnThank you again, my friend.
You've found him! Good. nnDo not blame him for his mistakes. He meant well for all of us. nnAll shall be... well... now.

When we arrived, this one should have known something was amiss.nnLurchers are not natural creatures. Evil magic enfused life into their rotting core.nnAdyssa will let the Bosmer's family know of this tragic loss.

You found an acolyte's robe? Splendid! That will serve nicely.nnOpen your bag and put it on. nnThat robe should allow you to wander through the caves without suffering any unexpected complications... like stab wounds... or dying.
When I find out who did this to meto usI'll kill him.
Where did Sarvyl go? nnWho will take care of me now?
Word to the wise. Stay away from those Ayleid ruins from now on.
Check near the entrance of the mines to find <<1>>. nnIf you can't find him, look for his smelly scamp, <<2>>.

I can feel it! I can feel the Master's Power! nnI feel it in every part of my body. Every! Part! And I must....nnWait. Why are you still here? Did I not give you a task?nnI'm communing with the infinite. Begone!
Have you gone mad? I heard your rampage all the way through the tunnels! nnThere you go! Barging in! Swinging your weapon around like a madm... like a...nnHey, is that the shard? nnExcellent.
You have our thanks!nnI hope Lord Sorick enjoys his prison cell.
I can make it from here. Just give me a minute to catch my breath.
Don't just stand around all day gawking. Get me out of here!
Help me! nnMy family ... the others ... it's unthinkable!
Zzzzz.

If it were up to me, I'd play Pierre and Claude off against each other. nnI could easily get them to murder each other... but if you'd rather just kill them off yourself, then that works, too.nnIt's up to you, <<1>>.
How could you set her loose? What did I ever do to you?
I hope Baron Sorick rots in a dungeon.
What's your birthsign, stranger? nnI was born under the sign of the Lover. Would you dare to kiss me now?nnThe stars are right.
Have you found that churl, Govyn? nnAfter you've taken care of him, meet me in the basement of the manor. nnI don't plan on leaving his estate without taking what's owed to me!
