Want to place a bet, pick up winnings, or make other types of... oh, it's you.nnAre you one of those troublemakers in need of a lesson? What'll it be, friend?

It's no use seeding the paddies again until I've figured out what's wrong with the plants that are already there.nnTo think! We used to be the most profitable salt rice farm in all of Deshaan! nnIt brings a tear to my eye.
Master Vinden ordered these. Now they're late.nnYou should take care of that.
Shaleen can't hide forever. nnHe'll be back.

Ah! Behold! A charm! I fathom the more cognizant husks will respond to it.nnI harbor a suspicion. Perhaps this trinket keeps the husks from simply wandering down the hillside. nnHow marvelous a sight that would be to behold!
My industrious companion has returned! nnHow fares the hunt?
Ervyna is dead!nnI hadn't thought it would be so easy.nnI hoped to feel something different, looking down at her body, but there's nothing there.
It's a vile job, no doubt about it. nnIf your research confirms what I suspect, this could signal a much bigger problem than a few oversized kwama.
The dirt gives the wine earthiness. It lacks complexity, though. You might lighten it up a bit with the herbs or some dried flowers.
Today, your actions have saved Aldsotha.
The soldiers are doing all they can to keep the temple protected. nnI just hope we can hold out until this battle's over.
I'm so worried about Endal. I haven't seen him since the attack. I can only hope he made it Mournhold before all of this happened.
<<1>> seems trustworthy enough. nnI'd believe her word any day.
The soldiers over there are excellent at broad strokes, but on occasion matters require... specialists. That is why we mages are here.
I was in such a hurry, I left my stall wide open. nnBildrin is a fool. That ruthless skinflint should have fled when he had the chance.

I fear the Daedric portal you closed allowed more of them through than I anticipated.nnThe Dremora Lord brought many under its control. nnImagine the numbers we might be facing if you hadn't acted when you did.

As I foresaw, the vessel has attuned to you. nnGo to the klat to the south of here. Anoint yourself and the elder with the venom you've collected.nnI cannot see past that task, for the end of your path lies within a dream.
The forest sends more of its plants to rip and tear at Zairrm-dar and his men, but the plants do not realize Zairrm-dar now has help!
You have more than earned the right to some answers. nnSit and talk a while. I will do my best to enlighten you.
Ah, you have come, it is well! But where is Lyris? Has she abandoned the cause at last? No, no. That cannot be, it is not written so.nnGo find our Titanborn. Bring her here.

Don't leave me to die like this! I only have one desire. I must apologize to my betrothed.nnI can only hope she'll take me back.nnMy bindings are behind me. Please, undo them, so I may see Brelayne again!

Once, <<1>>, we were a carefree couple. Then I turned away from Brelayne, not thinking or caring who I would hurt. nnThose were foolish days. I would be fain to forget them... yet I can never forget her.nnI am in torment.
We dare not let Aldsotha fall under the control of Daedra. nnAny assistance you could offer would be most salutary.
I heard you're helping <<1>> negotiate with the Imperials. nnDon't forget that <<2>> deal with the grave-robbing in the Bonebarrows.
Untouched! It's amazing. All of my wares are completely intact.nn I can't help but think it was because I stayed behind. nnPoor Hrenil fled, and they set fire to his stall!
I bet <<1>> wishes he could take back what he said to you before, eh?nnHis army is beaten. Well, not yet. But what you did in Haven means we can wear them down and push them off.
I hope Nelin finds something that makes him as happy as he made me.. before all of this... when we first met.nnIt's hard to believe, after all this, that we once were happy.
Who let you in? If you've come to kill me, turn around. Go back to the hole you crawled out of and tell your master Seagrave Titanborn is laughing. Go on!
I would have taken the coins, but to each his own.
It's good to see you again. Do you come with... relief?
The Abbot and Master Altien are safe, right?nnMay Azura watch over them, and may her blessings never falter.
The courier you seek is just south of our village. He's in our holding tent. nnYou may question him.
We can't create more Dreamless Potions without the Dream Shard.nnWithout those potions we, and the king, are vulnerable to the Supernal Dreamers.

Brother Hakam and I were novices together. How will I get on without him?nnOf course, returning Abbot Durak here is of even greater importance. I'm sorry to burden you with our troubles, but we're in dire need.
You have triumphed. The threat of Hosni at-Tura's Midnight Union is quelled.nnAnd we can return to watching and warding.
You smell like rotten flesh. You know that, right?
I'm not sure what we would have done without our scrolls.nnYou really should speak to Floran. I'm sure his matter is most urgent.
You must drink the Dreamstride Potion and free Durak from his dream.
Our allies have betrayed us. The Midnight Union are now enemiesand I failed to see it coming.
Those wards should work their magic soon.nnSlowly but surely, they'll work.
Please hurry. nnHurry before it's too late.
Good work! Once the flowers overwhelm Altmertown, they'll feel more at home.
You've avenged many lives lost in this place, and you helped us get back to work.
Impressive. Our sister's soul will return to the Coil, chastened by her defeat.
You must forgive him his ramblings, <<1>>. I can tell you what needs be done, and we'll leave the cryptic words behind. Are you ready?
You are no mere mortal. I can sense your spirit, even within this dream. It is powerful.nnPerhaps we will meet again.
You have more than earned the right to some answers. nnSit and talk a while. I will do my best to enlighten you.
We're not running a food service down here, but we have to keep our men and women healthy.nnI appreciate all the help. This might seem like a small task, but every bit helps.
Well, get on with it!
Have you found my brother?
Use the lure and kill the crocodiles it summons, then return to me.
Returning Wayrest to its former glory.will take hard work and dedication.
Drop the Capture Gem near wisps, lure them over it, and capture their power.
They're mad! Those cultists are mad! I knew nothing good could come from working with Daedra-worshipping scum like them.nnDid you get the key? We need to get out of here!
Have you found my missing maiden yet? nnI hope nothing bad's happened to her.
I may not have much time before they send another "brother" after me. nnPlease, help me get away from them.
Did you find a key? There must be one around here somewhere!
Captain Rama deliberately stole the totem to provoke the Stonechewers.nnAs long as that totem remains on the tower, we'll never be rid of those Goblins.
Have you succeded in your task? You would be among the few, if so.
Much better.
I sense his presence for the first time in death. nnThe rage that bound me here for so long has lessened... although it's troubling. nnI still feel anchored to this world.
I hope the souls of his victims have found peace.nnI can only hope. That's the only way I'll find peace.
I'm sure that when Ineri gave me the necklace, she had no idea how much harm it would bring.
I've told you all that I'm going to tell you.
My body, my foul, twisted body... you destroyed it.

You'll want to speak to Nardan or Dalynea. Show them the samples. Both of them have opinions on how the nix-hounds survive the tar pits.nnI'm sure they'll have ideas on how to go on from here. You'll have to decide for yourself.

Long ago, the kings of Daggerfall built their home atop Mount Dague, where they could look down on their valuable land.nnRunecrafters collect raw garnets from crystal shards. Since they're close to the mountain's base, they're easier to find.
She gave you boots? Boots? nnWhen your feet burn off, don't come running to me!
I'm quite confident my plan will work.nnThere's one thing I must warn you about, however. The smell that comes from those boots is rather wretched. nnHopefully, it won't startle the guar.
You have a problem?nnIf so, go report it at the Thalmor. They expect me to deal with their problems, so it's only fair I return the gesture.
The captain is sound asleep.
Well? What do you have to show for your efforts? nnI tire of waiting.
Were you successful? I hope you bring good news. The stress is almost too much to bear.
Thank goodness you're back. Did you have luck finding the lockbox?
Again, you have my thanks. If only I could be there to see the look on Hosni's face when you hand it to him.

Whatever poison this flower held has been drained.nnSomeday, we'll finally understand how this plant works. With our research and findings, we'll eventually find a way for our noble house to use this.nnThen our enemies will fear us.

What you learn will give you a new perspective. You'll learn the truth about those evil Ashlander witches. nnOur leader is up the pass. He awaits within the largest encampment of tents. nnHis name is Valeor.
You have returned! I admit I am surprised, I thought they had caught you when their messenger suddenly appeared.
This one is beyond help.
You have a gentle and generous spirit, stranger. Thank you for helping us.
Hic!
Were you successful?
Good, you've returned. nnDid you finish the task I asked of you?

You! Don't come near me!nnI saw what you did to the others. You had no right to do that. No right! Who are you to come into our camp and attack us?nnI know what you told Valeor, but I don't believe it. Those guards you killed, they were good people.
Please, eat up. There's more than enough for everyone.
The very idea of Stental accusing me makes my blood boil. I'd like to see the evidence!
I think it's time I took this matter into my own hands.

There is no suitable reward for what you've done. Sorry to say it, but your success has probably earned you more responsibility than reward. nnYou'll be hearing from me again sooner than you'd like. I apologize in advance.
What I do here will take some time.nnI'd recommend you go rest and help yourself to some food. I'm sure this all has been a tiring affair.
Ugurz has your money. I have no way to pay you.
Those bastards were lying to us! I should have listened to Ilerian.
We have nothing else to discuss.

If you're here to join the crew, today's not the day. The ship's still anchored out in the harbor. I'd write down your name, but I just don't feel like it. nnToo much to drink last night at the Cloudy Dregs .
Hilani hopes you will go to Pariah Abbey quickly.nnThe rumored attack could take place very soon.
Did you find Anabi yet? Hopefully, she's told you how dangerous these rabid alit are. nnDon't feel guilty putting them down. Think of it as an act of mercy.
I take a small measure of comfort knowing the effects of this so-called supplement are reversible.
You smell funny.
I sure hope we don't encounter any more Daedra anytime soon.
You learn to sleep with one eye open and a hand on your knife. Assuming your knife hasn't already been stolen.
Nice armor.
Ancestors protect me! That was the Wayrest Strangler!
Regardless of whether Teshmul is a spy or a thief, I'm determined to make an example of him. nnI'd like to see how he'd fare in pit of rabid alits.
I knew Jazha would win. I knew it!
I knew Jazha would win. I knew it!
I brought my best girl here to watch. She loves it. I can tell.
I'm here with a friend.
I knew Shanari would win. I knew it!
I knew Shanari would win. I knew it!
I'm so worried about Endal. I haven't seen him since the attack. nnI can only hope he made it to Mournhold before all of this happened.
You can save us and all of Menevia, but only if you can stop them before it's too late!
If you can thin the cultist numbers, we can get into the cave and rescue our allies.
I'll be all right. Please, find Christophe. nnIf the Supernal Dreamers succeed in fusing him with the Book of Circles, they can destroy Menevia... village by village!
If you found the key, unlock the cage.
I don't know what we would have done without your help. We couldn't leave the Book of Circles in the hands of these cultists.
Best keep your distance, friend. nnI wouldn't want you to catch the terrible sickness I've contracted.
I hope Mender Sarvyl didn't cause irreversable damage to the people of Deshaan.
Wow! The hero of the ring is passing out food? Would you sign this boar skin?
Wow! The hero of the ring is passing out the food? Would you sign this?
There are still some hungry people out there.nnIt looks like you weren't able to sell all of your fried boar skins.
Ha! Well done! That was an invigorating bout, <<1>>!
You were successful?
Thank Azura you're safe.nnDid you recover the Dream Shard?
I've never been so thankful to see a stranger in my life.
Thank you for helping us. I feared the worst.
Hopefully, the Vereansu will take this day's loss as a warning.
There's a sight for sore eyes, and surely a guiding light for any ships coming into port.nnYou saved the lives of a lot of sailors.
Hey! Are you <<1>>? nnSomeone gave me this mesage. It's got your name on it.nnI guess death finds us all.
Has this entire city gone mad?
I haven't heard from my family in Alcaire for some time now. They used to send word regularly. What do you suppose has happened out there?
You saved me, you saved my crew, you saved Elvira, and you showed up the most notorious slavers on the seas. nnI'd bet your name will be pretty well-known after this.

Excellent work! Your timing couldn't have been better. nnAs soon as the rocks crushed their Farseer, we were able to attack. The Vereansu were too shocked to know what hit them.nnOne thing distrubs me though....
You're back! Did you find my shipment?
What have we here? A guest who's wandered a bit too far from the party?
I've travelled up and down the Bjoulsae as a trader. Wayrest is the greatest city in Tamriel. Take my word for it!
Back from the Canulus Refuge! And that must be the Balac!nnWell go on, I don't know what's to be done with it. Give it to the old man.
Thank you for sending those goods to the people in the Uplands. nnI sure hope to hear from them soon!nnIt seems I can't rely on foot traffic to make this location worthwhile.
Thanks to you, we'll be ready for any battle that comes our way.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?
Now that the lighthouse has been relit, those ships are no longer in danger. They won't wreck when they enter the cove. nnGreat work, <<1>>!
Ervyna is dead. I hadn't thought it would be so easy.nnI hoped to feel something different. Something final. nnI feel nothing.

Some wizards are too far gone. They'll never recover from their madness. nnWe must take great care when we put these madmen to rest.nnThankfully, we won't see more souls fall prey to the evils Kellisa invoked. We owe you a debt of gratitude.
You'll need a key to unlock the cages. The first mate will know where they keep it.

It was it was Ma'jhad Kha. He saw me trying to escape I thought he had me, but then Elvira stepped innnThat girl's got sand, but she's no match for Ma'jhad Kha. He dragged her off toward the beach. You have to help her.
I know Duke Nathaniel posted me out here because I offended him. nnI can't do anything about that right now.
I am but a shell of a man because of that witch, but even with this small victory, I feel... vindicated.
If you can unlock the cage, I can run back to Koeglin Village on my own.
I'd ask the Duke for help, but I hear he's not himself lately. Then again, none of us have been.nnThe Daedra are driving us mad. I hope the Lion Guard is above this madness.
I recognize my better. You've bested me.
If someone doesn't stand up to Ra'ud and Lakana, they're going to disband Alcaire's guards. Mark my words!
Patrolling guards watch the cask of wine at the end of the docks.
You really descended into the device and destroyed it from below!
My uncle Danabi cared for me since I was little. nnWhen he fell ill, I knew he would survive. nnPerhaps I was right.
I am alive, yet afflicted with this disease. Is this a blessing or a curse?nnWhy was I saved? For what purpose was I exhumed from the ground?
No, this cannot be! nnDiviner Vemar, turned against the temple? nnWhat blasphemy is this?
You have the potion you need to beat Grul in a fight. nnSlaughter that Orc like he slaughtered my master!

You of all people should appreciate how we entertain our honored guests. nnYesterday, we set four servants against each other with clubs. Such a brutal spectacle!nnTonight we celebrate my engagement. Who knows what mayhem this occasion will inspire!
I am in your debt for saving my friends. nnOne day, when this school is cleansed and we are the masters, I hope to repay you.
Don't linger here. You've won this fight but the battle is far from over. Quickly! Go.
Was she there? Were you able to find anything?
I have finished preparing the remedy. Have you gathered the memories?

I won't authorize anyone to unload the Midnight Swell's cargo, nor will I allow anyone to resupply their ship. nnIf you're going to prove they're harmless, you'll need to bring me proof.nnI only believe what I can see with my own eyes.
I don't care what they say, these sailors are up to no good. They shouldn't be allowed to set foot in Koeglin Village.

You must believe your need is great, especially after enduring the hardships we have set upon you. nnThe threat to Deshaan is far greater than you know... and far worse than you could possibly imagine.
Patriarch Leyden's plotting has finally come to light. nnIt's a pity I couldn't uncover his plans before he fled.
The last heir of my family was left to die in this desolate place. nnAt least in death, we will be together again.

The dingies you need to burn are moored alongside their warship.nnThe ship lies off the western shore of the Imperial Landing beach. You can see it south of here. The bowspirit has a huge....nnWell, it's a big ship. See for yourself.
The mighty ogre has been vanquished! A feat of supreme skill!
That was magnificent. Congratulations  even if you are close to putting me out of a job.
Grab clothes from one of the houses, kill a few scamps, and hack off their limbs. nnOh, and watch out for those cultists. They're the ones behind it all! I can tell!
You have no idea how relieved I am. I finally have Gulpi back, alive and well.nnHe'll never leave my sight again... not until he's big enough to wear a harness!
Poor Constable Pascal. I have to admit thoughI sleep better at night knowing a Knight of the Flame is in charge.
Has this entire city gone mad?
Talk to Duke Nathaniel as soon as you can. Alcaire Castle is in danger.
I'm trying to find a way into the lower level. Somewhere down there, we'll find a way to stop Kellisa.nnMy divinations have shown me she's siphoning dark magic from an unknown source.
We treated the roots, but the groundwater was fouled. nnThe cleansing is not complete.
You have found it, have you not? nn'Tis strange. I can almost feel its presence. nnNo doubt that's expected when you've possessed something as long as I have!
Thank you again for your aid. I feel I owe you even more for not exposing me back there. They probably would have taken my life, so I am in your debt.
target: Thank you again for your aid. I feel I owe you even more for not exposing me back there. They probably would have taken my life, so Ti sono in debito.

source: I must remain here to make sure these people escape safely. nnThe path back to Mournhold is still fraught with danger.nnI owe them that much, after everything my men have put them through.

Before you go, I give you a final gift. I offer a warning.nnDare not attempt to go into the Abad through the obvious entrance. A small pass beside the river to the north will grant you access. nnUse caution. Tread carefully... or die swiftly.

The worst part of this is that these bandits sully the good name of the Knights of the Flame.nnIf our leader, Sir Hughes, was here, he'd charge out there and kill all the bandits himself just to make a point.

I have nothing more to offer you here. nnWe have other issues we must deal with now, such as your friend Naryu. He has chosen a perfect time to... disappear.nnI wouldn't trouble your pretty head with that right now.
Thanks, <<1>>. nnI shudder to think about what might have happened if you hadn't come along.
Mournhold is already a better city, now that our rogue brother is no more. nnLet's hope we don't have to deal with any more situations like his.nnSafe travels. Stay loyal.
Yes. nnYes, you've done your deed. nnThe Exalted Master is pleased. So am I. Be on your way.nnShadows hide you, wanderer.
You'll want to complete your other writs if you haven't already. nnYou can trust our Exalted Master, though. You must.nnShe'll hold true to her word, regardless of what she's promised you.
This should be far enough. I can make it back on my own from here.nnI wouldn't have made it this far without you.
The Stonechewers' breeding stock has been badly depleted by this foolish conflict. Leave me alone to contemplate this tragedy in solemn silence.
So Arcady can't pay his taxes because he was abducted by Dreugh, eh? Likely story.
S'Rashi hopes that this will be the start of a mutually beneficial relationship.
Those corprus things seem to have calmed down. nnI assume you're the one I should thank.
If you go up that ridge, please find Hlena.
May all the mothers and fathers of our mothers and fathers protect us.
Were you able to find anything in the ledger?
While watching Teshmul, you'll have the run of the place. None of my mercenaries should get in your way.
We will not forget your help. Thank you for freeing my companions.
You look like you have enough coin to risk a wager.
You look like you could use a drink, my friend.
I can't believe I came so close to being  whatever it was they were planning.nnI'm not exactly sure, but I'm glad you stopped them.
You look like I feel.
Why don't you come in and relax? Bide with us awhile.
You don't look like one of our usual customers.
Can I really spend all my time in a slump? nnEventually, all the losses have to lead to a win, right?
Did you see that last fight? That alit tore the other to pieces in a matter of minutes!
You look like you could use a good meal.
We were up in arms over nothing. I'm ashamed to call myself a Redguard.
The elixir will not immediately cure Semia, but her fever is breaking.nnTsajivi wishes you good fortune and better health.
We still need to kill the cult leader who's corrupted this circle of Dreamers.
Got a couple of lodgers from the ship's crew, and they're taking meals with me as well.nnThat's additional income I can use. And it's a lot quieter now that all the shouting has stopped.

The Kilarthu-Endel ruins are in an isolated valley southwest of Mournhold, nnFor the most direct route, exit the city to the south. Then follow the eastern path along the shore of Lake Thir.nnSince you've made it here, I know you can make it there.
It's not easy work, but it's profitable.
It's not easy work, but it's profitable.
My <<1>> is the finest lady you'll ever meet. nnShe understands me better than my wife does. More's the pity.
You brought her? You brought her here?nnIt's not that I'm unhappy to see her. Quite the opposite! nnYou'll need to escort her to the base camp, though. It's up near the entrance to the ruins.
It's not easy work, but it's profitable.
It's not easy work, but it's profitable.
What happened? Did you find Beltis?
I don't know the leader's name, but he'll certainly stand out from the rest. nnHe has to pay for all the good people his minions murdered.
They've nearly beaten the life out of the Captain. I guess Jharad didn't like his answers. You've got to help him. They're at the lighthouse!
Honor my dying wishes. Use a torch and set fire to the Inn, Pub, and Mayor's House. When you've finished report to a constable at the camp south east of here.
What?
Are you here with Saren?
Well? Did you tell that no good rascal what I'd do to him if he didn't leave my boat alone?
Hm?
I trust you to know your business! nnLet me know when you've dealt with those spirits.
Keep moving, stranger. There's nothing for you to see in this place.
Irne Oscent will inflate the cost of repairing his boat, but I'm not afraid of working. You tell him that.nnI don't trust him at all, but I'll do the work if he gets me released. nnTell him that.
You know, I used to hear horrible noises coming from the east across that small bridge.nnI don't hear them anymore.
Go out and clear this field of unwanted atronachs. Make room for their king!
Thank you for convincing Irne to set me free, <<1>>. nnI can keep an eye on him while paying off my debt, which is fine by me. nnI don't want him inflating the cost of the repairs, do I?
Hey, nice work with those cows. But where's Jerrick? He didn't get eaten too, did he?
Have you accomplished your mission? I can't rest until the Reachmen have paid for the atrocities they've committed.
It worked! I feared that touching the Water Stone would destroy one  or even both of us, but it didn't. nnWe merged. We are one. And we are both stronger for it.
I've worked with Lord Saren on other digs. nnIf I know him well enough, he'll stay down there until he finds a solution to this problem.nnI'll make arrangements to send down a hot meal.
I'll tell you whatever you want to know. Just get me out of here!
What's that? I smell oil! nnExcuse me. I believe the technical term is "mechanical lubricants."nnDo you have any Dwemer technology on your person? nnShow me. Please.
Lord Saren's impatience has cost us dearly.

The more we learn about the Dwemer, the more we realize how little we know!nnKnowledge is an ever-blooming rose. Each petal that opens itself to us reveals another hidden beneath it!nnFragrant knowledge abounds!
Stormhaven's been having some troubles of its own lately. nnSomething ails all of Tamriel these days.
I recognize my better. Leave me be.
I recognize my better. You've bested me.
I received a follow-up letter from Oortrel Fortress. nnLooks like I'll be able to spend more time here.
I should send a message to that drunkard Tharvil Avayon and relieve him of his responsibilities.nnSince he's not performing his duties, I might as well save a runner.
Brother against brother is a brutal conflict. nnEven in that confrontation, these knights found honor.
Thank you for coming. Hopefully I'll be well enough to travel soon.
<<1>> needs to learn his place. nnI cannot reprimand him too strictly, however. This is certainly an unusual plant.
You delivered the <<1>>? nnGood. Maybe I do have a chance at advancement after all!

Menas had some pretty dark days there for a while. I'm glad he survived. nnThank you for the news, tragic though it may be. I appreciate it. nnNot many would have gone out of their way to bring a final message to a loved one like that.
Take that jar of tunnelmites. Smash it in the hold of the Imperial ship docked to the south.
If they Imperials want to stay, it's only right that they should meet all of their new neighbors.nnI know some snakes who would love to greet them properly!
J'Hriss will inform the Altmer about the maps.nnThis explains how they held an advantage over us when they attacked. They knew exactly where we would be!
After surviving all this, I just may be able to make it in the wilderness afterall. I've certainly seen my share of experiences now.
I hope this attack doesn't mean more bodies for the Velothi Rivergraves.
The waters are muddy, and silt chokes. The surface is distant.
Please! Don't torture me! nnI'm done with the Empire.

This victory over the Imperials gains us more than a town. It strengthens our morale!nnM'zadha is wise to point out Rahira's overconfidence, but Rahira does not strike wildly at her opponents... especially not madmen like Vonov Sarturus.
How could she have left me? nnAfter all I've sacrificed for her, she abandons me like this? She leaves me here?nnI have the worst luck.
We meet again, <<1>>. nnI heard your investigation revealed a possible plot against the Hlaalu councilor. nnHave you left her to her own devices, then?
This is a nightmare!nnPlease say you have come to rescue me.
Razorvine Refuge received the good news. nnVillagers have begun to return to their homes.
Do you need assistence? If not, I'm afraid I'm busy at the moment. Damn, where are those sellswords? I can't fight them on my own.
What do you suppose those people down there are like? Do you think they like working in that mine?nnI wouldn't want to work in a mine. What would they do if they had a choice?
With the Warmaster leading us, reclaiming this town will hardly be a challenge.
This one will sing many prayers in your name.

The Dominion stands ready. Wer'e prepared for a counterattack.nnIf there was a reason they attacked Southpoint, we must find out. However, we don't have enough soldiers to send out on rescue missions.nnSee if you can help with that rescue.
This is the most boring post in the world. Nothing ever happens here.
You look suspicious. Who are you? What's your destination?
These weapons are of an unusual make. My sisters will be pleased.
If you need help, find us. nnKeeping these roads safe is our job.
Aren't you the one who slew Vonov? nnThank you for saving Haven!
You saved many lives this day. nnMay the moons shine on you.
I tried to get Denan out. I tried.nnI pulled and pulled and pulled and... and they...nnI got his torso. They kept the legs.
You're back! nnI made you something while you were gone. It's resting in the dirt over there, keeping warm.nnDid you find my father?
Borkul has already dispatched some Blackmauls to Wayrest for supplies.
I need to rescue my friends.nnI'm not sure if I can do it on my own, especially after that fool Gorvaro abandoned me.nnTruth be told, I'm probably better off without him.
Fill the bucket up at the well and take it to the tower to the east on the cliffs.
I love the smell of burning Imperial supplies. There's nothing else quite like it.nnI think they pack some kind of spice in those crates!
In all seriousness, my friend, Jillae and I are grateful. The best adventure is one that brings you safe back to the fire with your beloved by your side.
Do you have it? nnLet me see it! nnWow. It's shiny. I like it.
Do you have it?nnLet me see it! nnOoooh. Shiny.
Never again, honest! I've learned my lesson.
Please, talk to him. Listen to what he has to say.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! nnHow did that ring work out for you? Have you used it yet? nnYou really should, you know.
Attack J'raka's people and your corpse will burn.
Attack J'raka's people, and your corpse will burn.
Ah, you have come, it is well! But where is Lyris? Has she abandoned the cause at last? No, no. That cannot be, it is not written so.nnGo find our Titanborn. Bring her here.
Slay the loggers to the north. Hopefully, we'll drive the Imperials back. nnHe'll tell <<1>> more once they're done.

I could say 'it's not my fault' and it wouldn't be, but I can't help but feel guilty for not doing more to help that lost mage. The forest isn't safe no matter who you are, but I still feel like we threw a baby to the hoarvors.
You have returned. Are the wards active?
<The lost Altmer mage lies in a more peaceful repose than before. It is only a matter of time before the forest claims the body.>

While you were away, Ilia presented me with some herbs.nnI expected them to be bitter, but they were surprisingly sweet. Now I find that I am less tired.nnI must admit, my curiosity is piqued. I must learn the origin of these curious herbs.
Will you brave the horrors beyond that portal?
Look! When the magic disappated, that portal appeared!
So, did that mage did get himself killed?nnI'm so glad I kept an eye on Thylia here.nnShe might be worse than a baby in the forest, but she tells some great stories.
We tried to run when the Imperials attacked. nnSo many slain. So many gone forever.
Once the tonics are ready, we'll give them to all who have fallen ill.nnThe Imperials have already claimed too many lives.nnI'm not going to lose these wounded.

No, father! You can't go running about town! nnMy dear father, you are amazing, but you're quite troublesome. Thank the nice stranger!nnThank you, stranger. I'm always happy when our family is back together.
They have to let us in. They've got to let us in! nnThey're murderers if they don't!

You should check to the east. The Imperials are occupying Haven.nnThis one knows a seer left his books there, but Ra'Vashi does not know exactly where.nnBring some books to this one, so he may learn to use magic against his enemies!
Wyress Reinette is below. I suggest you speak with her, not me.
I felt a magical pulse a moment ago. Was that you? nnDid you defeat the Daedra inside the prison?
Thank you for braving the Thrambles to find me. nnI wonder if you would venture deeper to find the others....
Will the <<1>> listen to my offer?
Ho ho! What chaos! Baan Dar himself would be proud of such an endeavor.

Yes, hours are long and work is hard. nnAt least there are no itchy biting bugs in Stonefalls!nnEvery day in every way, this one's life gets better and better. Maybe next year he can have a day off. What luxury!
Why are we still down here?
I don't know why the other slaves are complaining. nnThis is exciting!
I don't want to die. nnI'm too tired.
Poisonous meat? You're not serious!nnI just sent a fresh meat home to my family....nnYou have damned them!
The water in one of these cups will invigorate you. The water in the other one is... uh... just water.nnFrom which cup will you drink? From which cup will I drink?nnThe suspense is killing me.
You look like you've seen a ghost! nnOh, wait... you really did see a ghost, didn't you?
I heard your voice, It was muffled, but I recognize it.nnI heard you arrange our freedom. Thank you. I owe you everything.
The Grahtlord is too ancient to remember any ties it had to the Bosmer. Anything that old has to be dangerous. nnThis day, you demonstrated courage and fair judgement.
I still have that letter you found. nnThanks again for taking the time to bring it to me.nnNot many folks would.
Looks like that dog has really taken a shine to you. You watch his back, and he'll watch yours.
No, I won't reconsider. nnLluthyne expects us to put our lives at risk for animals? nnI'd rather work the docks than get gutted by a poacher.
Give Lluthyne my love, won't you?
I've cursed my affliction every day since I went deaf. Who'd  have imagined it would save my life?
With our sage returned, peace between the Peatwalker and Mireblossom tribes is soon to follow.nnThank you, friend!
Where did these men even come from? What are they doing here? Can't you do something to stop them?
Have you completed your task yet?
Have you fullfilled your contract to the Fighters Guild yet?
Everything is ready at last.nnSadly, I have to combine several petitions into one ritual these days. There are so many who need my help, and I've no one who can help me.
My son's condition hasn't changed. I pray that Wyress Reinette's curative powers will save him.
No one knows who brought this plague to Evermore, but it's deadly.nnI pray that you do not suffer from it. I would not wish it upon anyone.
The river... check the river. Swim across if you have to, but find those damned Reach.
Ugh. What is that smell wafting around you?nnIs that you?
Do you have some claws for me?
Ah, I can smell that Motherwort from here! You've done well. The princess seems to be slipping deeper into her fever. Any further delay could be dangerous.
I've heard rumblings that the Minister of War is free, but she hasn't returned to the castle yet.
Thank you. I just need a moment to regain my strength. nnI've been tied up for so long! The pain of moving is just too much.nnYou might as well know: Once I can move, I'm going to run like blazes.
The Minister's deep within the dungeon. They separated her from the rest of the rabble.nnI doubt she minds the ghosts. Lady Ginie is very capable.
Are you ready to leave? nnI don't want to stay here any longer.
I appreciate your work, <<1>>. Give me a moment to catch my breath!nnGo back to the castle and thank Lady Isabelle for obtaining the <<2>>. I'll be there shortly.
Please remind the Minister that I was only doing my job. Her arrest warrant had the Queen's seal, too!
Four books, and you will have your reward. I warn you, do not attempt to read them. They may drive you mad.

Please, enjoy the juice I've given to you... but be sure to drink it responsibly.nnThe last time I shared this drink with a friend, she was locked away for doing some rather... um... "indecent" things in the middle of Elden Root.nnI've said enough.
I'm not surprised the Queen is seeking a Regent for Evermore. Her Majesty has always placed the city's well-being above her own.
Dunkarn Haven is in your debt, <<1>>. Thank you!
He threatened to kill me if I didn't let him take their bodies.nnHow was I to know he was a necromancer? I thought he was doing us a favor.
I feel terrible. Nothing matters.nnSoon, I'll find my uncle's body, when mine goes to join his.
I pray they made it out safely.
The battered spriggan has stopped moving.
The stench of death is heavy upon you. I take it your assault goes well?
<<1>> sent you? To be honest, I did not trust him when he came to us. Thank you for proving me wrong.

If she's been caught, she probably stayed in her wolf skin. Be on the lookout for any Reachmen with wolves nearby. Kill the handlers you find.nnThe wolves should run off, once their handlers are dead. If they don't, they're too far gone to save.
Can it be? I thought you were a vision... the sickness playing tricks on me. But no! You are here, and you have the cure. Quickly! Give it here.
The potion will work soon. I'm sure of it.nnIf only my daughter had lived a little while longer, she'd be cured, too.

I know single combat seems an odd way to solve a tax dispute, but its use goes back generations in Evermore. Some say it's barbaric, but I couldn't do away with it even if I tried.nnWell, then, what was the outcome? Who won?
You're back... and in one piece. Impressive!nnHow did you fare with your task? Is the listening stone in place?
You got lucky, but don't think battles will always go your way.nnI'll mourn my fallen comrade later, when this ship finishes its business and is on its way again.
The sooner we leave Evermore, the better. We might have won this time, thanks to you, but what about next time?
You'll find the Hortator's grave east of the entrance here. nnYou should hurry, lest the priestess changes her mind.
Did you destroy the altar and kill that bastard witchman?
We did it! Nice fighting, champion.

I know single combat seems an odd way to solve a tax dispute, but its use goes back generations in Evermore. Some say it's barbaric, but I couldn't do away with it even if I tried.nnWell, then, what was the outcome? Who won?
If you haven't already, speak to our wise woman. nnHer hut overlooks the rest of the village.
I'm very sorry, but the race has already started.nnYou'll need to come back and talk to me when this one is done!
Vonov became a lich. nnWe actually assisted his ritual by slaying him.nnRahira trembles with rage.
Please travel to the ruins west of here. nnCollect some of the glowing whitestones. I need them to identify a certain ritual.
I'm bored.
Imperial spies could be lurking nearby. nnYou will excuse me if I cannot discuss the weather with you.nnYou may pass.

I should be glad we got away, but I'm too angry to think! They've taken the garrison? nnThe brutish swine! If there's one thing I do before I die, it's going to be spitting on the corpse of that cowardly wench Septima Tharn.
I hope that you stopped that necromancer from causing troubles within the city of Evermore. We've suffered enough lately.
You bring warning about an attack? If only you'd come a day earlier...

No need to say it. I can read the truth in your face.nnAdrusa was so young. I sent her to Senie thinking it would be safer there.nnDespite that, I suspect it's better to grieve than to never know. Thank you for risking your life on my behalf.
It's convenient that Othrenis is located south of here. nnHave you seen a city of the dead before? nnHopefully, Marea is still there.

Scamps are still swarming out of that maw in the mountainside.nnI know those caves are large, they can't be big enough to fit them all.nnMark my words. There's something unnatural in the heart of that volcano.
We cannot leave the box in Reachmen hands. Heed my warning. Retrieve it, but do not open it.

Scamps are still swarming out of that maw in the mountainside.nnI know those caves are large, they can't be big enough to fit them all.nnMark my words. There's something unnatural in the heart of that volcano.
I need to pause a moment to brief these guards on the situation within the dungeon.nnPlease go on ahead to the castle.
We must turn the afflicted away from our gates. This grieves me.nnStill, that's better than letting Ashkhan's warriors slaughter them.
Have you completed your task yet? I thirst for knowledge.
I... do not know what to say. nnI feel so foolish now! nnWhat precious times we lost out of fear for an unkind word!
Goodbye...
You have the skull. Force Ergend to face the truth.
What is that you have... oh. Yuck. Yuck! Get it away from me!
<The princess is sleeping once again. It seems Gurles' cure was only temporary.>

I prayed and prayed for a cure. The Tribunal will do nothing for me!nnThese Ashlanders worship a holy Daedra, and they don't fall sick. nnIf the Tribunal won't cure me, maybe Boethiah will... or Mephala... or Azura!

I prayed and prayed for a cure. The Tribunal will do nothing for me!.nnThese Ashlanders worship a holy Daedra, and they don't fall sick. nnIf the Tribunal won't cure me, maybe Boethiah will... or Mephala... or Azura!
They have to let us in. They've got to let us in!nnIf they don't, they're murderers!
We've so many tasks given to us, it's a wonder anything gets done.nnCome back when you've completed the contract, <<1>>, and I know we'll have more work for you.
Did you make it inside her hut? nnDid you find the cure?
That was terrifying! The poor spirit - so helpless. I'm glad you were here to defend us both, but you can rest easy now. It's my turn to help.
Thank you for your aid, champion. The Viridian Sentinel once protected against such dangers, but his time is at an end. The rebirth is at hand! And the princess can now fulfill her promise.
Kynareth smiles on your efforts. Please hurry.
I hope Wyress Reinette will send a curative spirit to me soon.
You've collected the offerings. Good. Take them to each urn and burn them.
All this bloodshed could have been avoided if <<1>> had accepted my offer. nnWas the building really so important to them? Was it worth dying for?nnNow her tribe has nothing.
Used to be, the Viridian Sentinel shielded this land from trolls and their ilk. Now... well, Gurles says the Sentinel's time is nearing an end, which doesn't bode well for this forest.

The rope should be long enough for you to snare them from far away. nnThey're wily little creatures, so remember to keep your wits about you.nnYou'll find Ralmas outside of this building. He's refused to abandon the barn.
You found him? Is he hurt badly? nnHe won't leave until his duty is complete. I know him too well. nnWhat a stubborn fool.
Thank the Three! You've found my supplies! nnTake them to the captain with my apologies. nnI'll try to make it back to Olyvna and return to Davon's Watch.
Hurry to Sir Dencent. He's on the center dais of the graveyard to the north.
No priest can countermand a king. This matter is settled.
Do you honor the Divines? If so, help me.

I can't handle the number of injured soldiers I have to heal, and we have no way to move the injured from here. nnIf the cliff racers continue to harass us like this, we'll have to abandon the fort.nnThat would be a death sentence for all of us.
I hate you.
Do not raise my son. Do not consign him to that fate. Let me help you instead.
It was the only choice. I am glad you saw that as well as I.
You honor the Divines. Queen Therese thanks you.
If we didn't follow the traditions of our ancestors, would we still be Kargesh?
If we didn't follow the traditions of our ancestors, would we still be Kargesh?
If you hadn't come, I'm not sure what those Ashlanders would have done to me.
I'll have to swing by Norus' tent once I've finished going through these supplies. nnLet's just say I was less than kind when I thought he answered my inquiry about supplies with a joke.
I almost don't know where to start. nnIt's been so long since I had real supplies!
I hope the supplies will last us for awhile.... Between the Orlishkaarn and Mt. Senie, it's a wonder we have anything left.
The guar bring us life. Their herds feed and clothe us.
May your kills be quick and many.
target: Che le tue uccisioni siano rapide ed innumerevoli.

source: Hrmph. Well. Thanks. For your help. I guess.
What a magnificent chase! nnTell me, <<1>>, did you like playing the Huntsman?
Wealth beyond measure, friend.
The book is blank, and many pages have been torn out.
The book is blank, and many pages have been torn out.

My roots burrow hungrily into the earth, as if the loamy soil were my only need. nnBut I feel a hollowness that I cannot abide. I see a being here I want to remember, but when I try to think, there is nothing.

The pages you've collected seem to fit perfectly into the book. With everything in place, the meanings are coherent. Many details fill the pages exploring the aggressive turn of the once passive creatures - each note signed by an "<<1>>".

A stench, similar to that of soured food, fills the air when the coffin is opened. The rotted remains of what could only be a Dunmer are scattered and broken within the coffin.nnThe only thing missing from the remains is a head.
This guard is dead.
You hear a few low moans from the other side of the door and footsteps coming towards you.nn"Do you have our food yet?"
You hear shuffling and coarse whispers coming from inside. After a moment, someone inside speaks. nn"You've proven yourself trustworthy, but you still need to feed us. We're starving."
You hear shuffling and coarse whispers coming from inside. After a moment, someone inside speaks. nn"You've proven yourself trustworthy, but you still need to feed us. We're starving."
When Virgil returned, he told us Captain Renoit was willing to see reason.nnDespite that, his soldiers are still besieging our mill.
I stopped hearing her yelling a few minutes ago. nnWhatever you've done, we appreciate it.
I already told you! I'll get to the little wretch when I can!nnThe captain will just have to wait. nnI'm in no hurry to deal with another one of those wretched beasts.
The gall of those Ashlanders is unbelievable. Openly worshipping Daedra in plain view of Ebonheart! It's like they want to be slaughtered.
The Imperials are holding Bankgorai Garrison. nnUnless someone stops them, they'll roll over the rest of Bangkorai.
You've put them on the defensive.nnWe need to finish this.

We will hold the survivors.nnThey pollute Boethiah's sacred space, but they will be useful during negotiations.nnThe rest of our tribe is in the conclave to the east. They'll be glad to know of our victory, temporary though it may be.
I'm glad to see you're alive and well.nnWhat news do you bring?
I'm surprised you got anything out of that n'wah. nnIf it were up to me, he'd pay for what happened to the Hortator.
They're nothing more than wild animals. nnThey live in crude huts and slaughter without reason. Sometimes I wonder if they're truly Dunmer.nnMaybe they're some other kind of creature entirely.
Remember your promise. nnIf they won't release me voluntarily, I'll still expect you to do your part.
Gurles Edier is the current Viridian Sentinel. He has been hiding how ill he is. I think you should keep a close eye on him.
I didn't realize we were out of dried belladonna berries. nnThey'll be easy to find now that the trees have been cleared away.nnUnfortunately, there were still a few wolves in the area. Be careful.
The captain is wise to heed my words. nnI hope he's honorable.
Well, you've made it back in one piece.nnWhat news from the Orlishkaarn?nnDid you speak to the Ashkhan?
This land is my responsibility now, mine to watch over and care for. Should you encounter a truly dire threat in your travels through Bangkorai, you may use that charm to call for my help.
Thank you for helping Loraine with those poultices. They'll save a lot of people.
I'm not ashamed to admit I'm relieved. nnAs Queen Therese gave a direct order, Sir Dencent and I may ignore King Eamond.nnTell Father Hurrent what you've decided. Let us be done with this.
I need to reach the soldier's camp safely.nnThey've been wary of anyone approaching from the mill.
You should speak to <<1>>, north of here.
Enter text related to the Shrine.
Is it true there is a camp of Ordinators across the river?
It should be me lying cold on the ground.
Have you helped set the spirits of my fellow soldiers to rest?
I tried to fight. nnThey had swords. I had a shovel.
My best friend died in a fight. nnI say we cut the prisoners' throats. They're just heretics!nnTthe Tribunal might even reward us.
The trail ahead is clear, <<1>>. nnYou may walk among the Huntsmen as one of us.nnApproach without fear.
I am saddened to hear of Beven's troubles. nnBeven and those at Kerbol's Mill are some of Hircine's most devoted followers.
There you are! nnI sure hope you've found something, because they're on to us. We nearly got our heads lopped off back there.nnWe need to finish our business here. Is that an Orc prisoner?
I fear the Dunmer will strike at the heart of the coral before I have a chance to protect its young.nnHave you found many polyps yet, my friend?
That was fantastic! I haven't had that much fun in ages! nnYou've brought joy to this old regent's heart.
I will not last much longer, so I beg you to kill the beasts quickly. nnI want to see their dead flesh harvested before I join them in death.
I'm on my way back to Garland now. nnI'll be sure to let him know what I asked you.

The Dunmer have caught themselves in the anemones of the coral reef.nnWithout proper protection, we can't extricate them from the tentacles' grip.nnFortunately, you're coated enough to withstand the tentacles. Let's go find one of those mercenaries!
Yes? Please do not overstimulate the king. nnHis health wanes, and he needs rest.
You must assist your friend. You must help Farah.nnShe abandoned all caution and ran north to the Rotting Tower.nnShe left to confront Vonov alone.
One more step, and we'll find Vonov.nnHe won't even suspect what's happening around him!nnVengeance will be paid in full. He'll pay what he did to me... and my father.
<<1>>! It's really you!nnWhen I heard your name spoken around the village, I was thinking, "This must be a coincidence. It can't be the same <<1>>!" nnYet here you are. It's good to see you again.
Somehow we've made this work. nnWe're not clear of the danger yet, though.
You've gained insights into the chaos stirring in my homeland.nnTell me. I must know.
Now that almost looks cheery, doesn't it?
Yeah, I killed one of the Dres. What of it?nnYou would have kill one too, if you'd been beaten by that bastard every day.
My hair is so itchy. I don't know if its from the ash or if its lice.nnMother Mara, I wish I could just hack it all off and soak my head for an hour.
Those hairless slaves! All the time, they complain about the wind. nnThey should grow a nice fur coat, eh?
The last Dunmer who owned this one sent her to the mines. nnThis one still has dirt under her claws.
The Imperial Houses will bring these Dunmer curs to heel. nnThen we'll extract bloody vengeance for the murder of Emperor Reman.
The sky is too big here. It's pressing down on me.nnIf only we had a roof to sleep under.

I'd rather be on patrol than manning the fort.nnSince the hortator took control from the captain, we've been shorthanded.nnMaybe the hortator will put me on escort duty for his shipments. That would be a pleasant change of pace.
You found our food!nnSo, who did this?

I've issued orders to tighten the watch on <<1>>. They'll never forage to the north, and to the south, there is only sand.nnIf all goes well, they'll be boiling the leather in their shoes for soup within a month.
Hurry and save our leader! Don't worry about us. We'll fend for ourselves.

I'm glad you both made it back. Josselin and I are  close. I don't think I could lose her after losing Eamond.nnToo many friends are dying around me, and I'm here with all my powers, helpless.nnExcuse me. I must keep my mind clear and focused.

If you're looking for supplies, I'm afraid I can't offer you any.nnI'm undermanned and overworked with tracking the hortator's shipments in and out of the fort.nnWhat possessed him to commandeer a remote outpost for his base of operations?
More reports from Captain Athelyn? nnI have a schedule to maintain and shipments to oversee.nnHis concerns are not my concerns, and our lives will remain that way.
Take the antidote to my son.nnYou have to save him!
I'm impressed. I heard we have you to thank for fending off the Imperials from our supplies.
Suram will be angry with me.nnI told them both it would be a simple mission. Now her blood is on my hands.
I don't have the strength to escape.nnGo on without me.
My son... so it is true. nnWhy do you disturb me, <<1>>? nnDo you too wish to sink your blade into my chest, putting me out of the misery that consumes me?
If you can rid of us this crying, many of us will sleep easier at night.
I promise, no more tricks from Old Zad!nnIt was wrong of me to steal that food, and I know it.nnI swear it won't happen again.
Why are you rooting through our things?
My bonds are loose. I can escape at any time, but I'll stay a while longer.nnSomeone needs to keep an eye on those Reachmen.
I don't have the nerve to attempt an escape.nnI'd rather live as a slave than risk getting killed.nnGo on without me.
Have you found the metal Zhavas has lost?
Ah, my son! He'll be a better heir than I ever was, if he can learn to relax once in a while. nnLook at how my beautiful Altmer queen looks at him. He doesn't even notice!nnI'm almost jealous.
Be careful. <<1>> has guards who only work for him.nnThey're just as corrupt as he is. If they spot you, they won't be terribly kind.
Did you find anything? nnI haven't taken my eyes off that house since you went inside.
Any word about my mother?nnI'd like to know what became of her, but I wouldn't dare try to escape.nnI just know I'll get caught. Then they'll beat me more.
Barnabe talks to all the prisoners to gather information about the Imperial forces.nnYou'll find him with our current prisoner in a tent atop the hill.

He's been questioning me already. I won't tell either of you anything.nnThe Imperial Army will crush Evermore's puny military. I'm surprised to find you haven't retreated all the way back to Wayrest by now. Cowards!
You look familiar.nnSay, you haven't seen a pipe around here, have you?

The Imperial Army's been staying inside the Garrison.nnWe're lucky that <<1>> caught this one lurking outside our camp's perimeter.nnLike most Imperials, he's not willing to talk. I think we can change that.
Don't forget. <<1>> wanted to see you.
Go. Look at my son.nnMy boy was once the strongest in our village. He was my blood. He carried my name proudly.nnLook into his dead eyes. Tell me you do not understand my sorrow... and my rage.

Elvasia knew the tinctures being sold weren't doing any good.nnShe heard rumors of a shrine to Boethiah that's granting to immunity to Kagesh Ashlanders. She left at once.nnEven the slightest chance is worth taking if it means saving a life.

The ordinators took over the shrine? nnWell, at least the saltrice will do some good for Ebonheart's poor.nnThese Ashlanders came from a conclave to the east. Maybe I'll go there.nnThey could have a cure, right?
Did you find Listian?nnHe hasn't returned yet. My friend is truly beginning to worry.nnI'd like to have some news to deliver.
Did you deal with the chest and what it contains?
If they catch us, they'll sacrifice us.nnI'll stay here and take my chances.
Its fear is overwhelming. I need time to soothe its spirit.
Your slaying of <<1>> was  adequate. Step closer.nnI won't even liberate you from all that stifling skin you wear. I generally find your kind slightly less grotesque when peeled. Slightly.
I feel like we've become fast friends, <<1>>. nnYou... didn't bring anyone else with you, did you?
I've never been so close to death before.nnIt's as if I could feel the hand of Arkay resting on my shoulder.
Did you have any luck making the cure?
I have no wish to take this conflict further, but until I can assure my queen that werewolves no longer threaten us, I have no choice but to maintain our siege.
Now that we've helped Captain Renoit's soldiers and the secret is out, I hope he'll release my brother.nnThere's no reason to hold Virgil any longer!
They'll force some of us to fight in their army and the rest will become slaves or sacrifices.
You'll find silver bark on the trees to the north.nnBeware the wolves!
My friend, have you had any luck? nnI'm afraid I need the coin very soon.nnI have to settle some of my other... expenses.
We went to the mill to try and take the cure by force, but the mill workers attacked us. These werewolves may intend to destroy Evermore.
Please, save these people, if you can.nnThey cured my brother and took us in when no one else would.
Ferise and I go back a long time. I'm a bit hurt she thought I would not understand. I will have to buy her something nice to celebrate.
The Dunmer may never understand the delicate balance we've negotiated.nnThey need not. I believe we are now in a position to make them listen.
Thank you for delivering our offering. Hircine will be pleased.

Now that the woman's dead, I can set my mind to the future.nnWho am I kidding? A crippled slave in the heart of Morrowind? The best I can hope for is a quick death when troops put down this little rebellion.nnStill, I outlived that damn witch.
Janise is alive? Thank Mara. nnYou've eased my troubled mind, <<1>>.nnI hope she gets here soon.
You've very kind to come all this way. nnMay the Divines bless you, <<1>>.
The entire manor is in mourning. nnI have no time for the likes of you.
Serjo Belaal cut such a dignified figure. Her demeanor was so noble. nnTruly, we are diminished by her departure.nnYour pardon. I must dab away my tears.
I had to sell the rest of the supplies if I wanted to turn a profit. nnCurse these Ebonheart peasants! nnN'wah! Each and every one of them!
You impressed Rahira, <<1>>.nnRahira is unsure if this one could have defeated Vonov alone!
I should have known something like this would happen sooner or later. nnAnd the guards do nothing? nnThey've made it quite clear what they think of us.
Thank the Eight. You have my book.nnI thought the Imperials burned it!
The Imperial archmage must die.nnThe only thing worse than an Imperial army is an an Imperial army with giant stone pets.
Please tell me you found the medicine! nnI'm sure they wouldn't throw it out.nnIt's very... potent.
What happened? Some of the wood orcs just ran out of here and the Tree here feels different somehow did you succeed?
No. No. nnCan't talk anymore.nnRead the note.
What Ovis must have thought of me all this time!nnI hope he'll see reason and speak with me.
I fear Serjo Belaal has been found dead in her chambers.nnHer murder must have been vicious. Her corpse and room were in disarray.nnI have no doubt. One of our escaped slaves did the deed.
The Hidden will throw off the Imperial lash, no matter how many must die.
It's time!
I'm glad that Elder Ahbeh accepted you. nnI suspected she would.
Another has come before us, one who has done much for our people.

These others were lucky to free themselves. nnThat's really our fate as Argonians. The Dres hid us away in the canyons. Other races, they could traffick in openly.nnAh, well. We'll all feed a tree in the end.
Have you done what I asked?nnThe powder is harmless, I assure you.
Now that we've collected enough blossoms, we'll need to prepare a few bodies for the ceremony.
We sent our swiftest runner to the capital at Mournhold.nnHe's taking the manacles you gathered.nnThe Great Moot will know of House Dres' treachery.
Well done!nnThe Redguard bodies have been purified. Their souls have been ushered into the afterlife.nnYou've helped preserve the balance of nature in the Bone Fields.
We have the Dres by their unmentionables. nnOnce those shackles are placed before the Great Moot, the other Dunmer Houses will be shamed into taking action.
Praise to the Three, sera. Can I get you anything today?

The news of Serjo Belaal's passing is distressing.nnThe slaves of the Dres have grievances. Settling them with the cold-blooded murder of a noble lady is unacceptable.nnAlmalexia will show the guilty little mercy. We must have order.
Serjo Aryon says I don't need to polish her chitin, but I think she deserves it.

I wish the silt strider father bought were big enough to ride.nnI'd get on its back and let it run until the dust and the wind and the stench of sulphur is far behind me.nnI've never seen grass. They say the ground is covered with it to the south.

If Serjo Violyne ever came to harm at the hands of those stinking n'wah slaves, House Father Aryon would let us clean up this town.nnNot that I wish the girl any harm, you understand. nnShe's very... sweet. Not a bit of her mother's steel in her.

I wish I could be one of Vivec's Buoyant Armigers, but I'm not clever enough. nnMy poems are too pitiful to show to Serjo Viol. I've never shown them to anyone!nnStill, I'm a good fighter, and I try to be honorable. Just don't ask me for a sonnet.
The grave! nnIt must be empty. nnHe... he can't be inside!

Rosamund was pretty nice. She let me touch her arm.nnA lot of the slave women won't anymore. Dunmer men like foreign women, especially the gentle, quiet ones.nnI think that's because their women are cold and sharp... more like daggers than pillows.

Sometimes at night, we hear wailing from the east. nnWhen I was a boy, my parents told me it was wind blowing through the canyons.nnWhen I was older, they told me about the slave pens the Dres built there.
We're fortunate to have such a devout House Father as Serjo Aryon. nnNo one could question his faith in the Tribunal!

My daughter is as weak-minded and feminine as any Altmer man. Don't assume I share her weakness.nnHow my husband dotes on her! It sickens me! nnIf I had known she'd turn out, I would have cut her from my loins instead of bearing this shame.
I believe my wife is dead, but not knowing the truth makes my grief worse.
Vusara must be stopped. nnIf you can find her, I can give you the means to penetrate her wards.
You killed Curio. Thank the Eight!nnHurry, get out of here before they catch you!
Thanks to you, I'm back inside the walls of <<1>>!nnAnd I took revenge on a few straggling Imperials on my way here!
Greetings, <<1>>.nnIt's nice to see another strong guild member around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that.
I'm counting on you to pull your weight around here. Don't let me down.
Have you completed your task yet? I thirst for knowledge.
I hope those Akaviri wraiths don't give you too much trouble.nnThey look awfully formidable to me, especially considering the state of our friend, <<1>>!
Have you completed your task yet?

My business wouldn't be troubled if it wasn't for those magmer.nnWhen they first appeared, no one knew what they were. All the workers fled. Luckily, so did my competition.nnPlease tell me you have what I requested.
Were you able to find my children?nnI know Danea will need help bringing her brothers back.
I can't imagine the stress our Aunt Salori must be going through. nnOur father passed away from illness several months ago.nnNow she spends so much time worrying about us.
Danea told me what you did. nnThank you for helping us.
Thanks to you, I'm myself again.
Someday I'll get a proper budget, one that allows me to keep the streets lit and swept clean.nnAnd as long as I'm dreaming, I'd like to discuss social theory with a Dwemer Tonal Architect.
Tyl told me you've been busy. nnI've heard tales of your courage!nnWherever problems are solved, I expect to find you.
Now I have to go back to the ruins and bury my sister.nnBy Mauloch, this is a dark day.

I understand if you're needed elsewhere, but you're welcome back here whenever you like. nnWardens are valuable, and you're quite skilled.nnIf you're headed into Gil-Var-Delle, I wish you luck. It would be a shame to lose someone like you.
That strange girl entered a hut to the east. nnTread carefully, friend.
Were you able to find them?
It's a shame the commoners of this town don't share your willingness to aid the common good.nnYou're an exemplary ciitizen, stranger.
Watch your words while you're in the keep. nnThe guards are quick to anger.nnThey won't ask questions until they've drawn steel.
That was an excellent show of strength, <<1>>.
Yoon is thanking you, <<1>>!
I sent my servants to look for my father's body. nnWhen it can inter him discretely, we'll place him in our ancestral tomb.
When my brothers' souls were trapped in the gems, these statues rose from the ground.nnYou'll find Thadan's gem to my left. Threval's soul gem is to my right.
Do you think they're going to evacuate Heimlyn Keep? nnIt's right up there, perched on the edge of the volcano.nnWith all the smoke coming out of it lately, I don't know why anyone would stay.
Did you notice they fixed the street lights? nnI wonder how long it will be before the skooma peddlars break them again.
These are troubled times, my friend. The best thing to do is to keep yourself safe.
Kill the risen! Lead them home!
Your rolls have been made. nnLet's hope you've rolled right!
How's the hunting going?
Could I interest you in a game of chance? nnI'm told I have terrible luck, but maybe today will be different.
How about a little game of chance? nnI have terrible luck, but that's bound to change, right?
Remember, throw the scamp heads into the nascent portals.nnThen meet me in the cave to the north when you're done. If Azura favors us, I'll have rescued Master Muzgu by then.
The poison vial is over there, next to the candles.nnBring it to me.
You think you have nothing? Oh, my friend, you always have your soul.

My brother is wasting his time. The raw materials are plentiful here, and their owners are exceedingly poor. It's a buyer's market.nnHe always wanted to be someone's savior. He should follow his avarice.

<You've found a dead body. This Dunmer recently met his death.>nn<Judging from his clothes, he was a farmer.> nn<A shovel beside him looks just like the one Faynis gave you. You aren't the first he's sent to get his father's fortune.>
By the Three! If you don't cease your leering and leave this palce....
Excuse us. nnThis is a private matter.
Your pardon, sedura. I must get through here!
Now that you've investigated the cairns, you can find the crazed spirit of my great-grandfather and put it to rest.

I had a strange assignment the other day. nnSerjo Heleran asked a few of us to pick up the body of an old skooma addict down in the Gutter.nnShe met us outside town, but I don't know where she went with the body. Say, you think she's a necromancer?
I hear they caught another heretic the other day. Some Argonian showed disrespect for the Three.nnThey should have placed his head on a pike! That would have warned those nonbelievers!
Good luck in there, <<1>>.
The miners must be seeking a shred of hope.nnYou'd be a far more fitting messenger than I would be.

The Dres have shipped a lot of slaves up to Heimlyn Keep over the last year. nnThey must be doing some kind of massive construction project to need that many bodies.nnWe're betting it's a new forge works. What say you?

They complain about the volcanoes here, but I was in Vvardenfell when Red Mountain exploded.nnThey say you could hear the roar as far away as Imperial City.nnI don't know if it's true, but every tree and mushroom for a hundred miles was knocked down.
If what you say is true, you'll have to find the antidote to the poison before it kills <<1>> and <<2>>.
You sure taught the Reachmen a lesson!nnI bet they'll think twice before taking more captives.
I don't care what you do in the Gutter. Out here, we keep things peaceful and orderly.nnKeep your eyes on the ground and your hands in your pockets.nnThen we'll get along just fine.
You've got it! nnQuickly now! Throw it down that fissure before anyone sees you.
You're always welcome in Kragenmoor, citizen... unless you're carrying more skooma into the Gutter... in which case, we'll kill you.nnI'm sure you aren't. Am I right?
Not the face!
Going for a ride? Will you be needing a boost up, then?nnShould I get the "special" ladder?

I had to return my last shipment of slaves. People just don't want Bosmer any more!nnThey're amusing for a brief time, I'm sure, but they're too slight for heavy labor and too mischievous for household duties.
Never forget. We are Dunmer, the blessed of the Three. nnWalk with your head high, as Saint Roric would. nnKnow that you are superior to your foes.
There's less smoke coming out of Mount Heimlyn now! nnI hope that's a good sign.
Are the necromancers dead?
The damned dreugh are everywhere, and these citizens have lost their minds!nnThey're attacking dreugh bare-handed. I've saved as many as I can, but that last dreugh wounded me. Help!
If you're going in to meet Inadan, you have to perform the signals precisely. nnIf you make a mistake, he won't show up.
The search for the Grandmagister continues! nnIn the meantime, I can spare a moment to speak with you.

I have a happy, fulfilling life. A beautiful wife! Intelligent children! Plenty of power!nnDo you know why? It's because I accepted the Almsivi as my personal saviors.nnOnce you accept the Almsivi, you'll never be homeless, powerless, or alone.
The arrogance of the Dres makes living in Kragenmoor insufferable.nnOn the other hand, the fact that the affliction hasn't spread to Kragenmoor mitigates that somewhat.
Are you making progress with your suit?

We have no proof that House Dres is behind these latest atrocities, but all signs clearly point to their involvement.nnTake those documents back to Dres.nnI'd love to see their faces after we find that proof.
I hope you were able to help the pilgrims.nnTo think of it! Some have travelled so far with dreams of miracles, only to receive a blessing in its place.
Let me use the writ to break the curse. nnOnce I liberate the land I conquered long ago, we'll finally be free.nnChoose me, and I'll fight by your side to free Bangkorai from the Imperials!
The works? Fixed? No, that can't be. Can't be.nnI can't leave. Not until it's fixed. They were depending on us. On my brothers and I. I'm so worried. What's happened since we left?

Collecting the ingredients you require shouldn't be too hard.nnThe Almsivi blossoms have opened quite nicely in the fountain below us.nnGathering scathecraw may prove a bit trying, but it grows profusely outside of these walls.

I didn't think I'd see you again! I want you to know my sister is buried.nnI'm on the trail of the murderer now. It seems one of Ogambu's experiments went awry.nnDon't worry, though. I'll hunt that beast down soon enough.
Did you find it? Did you recover my lost experiment?
The dead still walk this Hall, <<1>>. nnYou can learn from their wisdom.
I don't think I will survive much longer. I can barely keep down water.nnThovasi must be mistaken. This cannot be a simple poisoning. Must I simply wait this agony out?
Verro will die.nnThen souls of our brothers and sisters will finally be free!
Have you found the antidote? You must hurry!
I hope the Diviner was not too cross. nnShe was always so kind to me, and it pains me to think I disappointed her. nnEven her kindness could not compel me to stay.

All right, I'll admit it. I get excited when there are loud sounds. nnRevi said I once tore a mer's throat out when he whistled too loudly. Not long after that, he sent me here to get better.nnHe's crazy.
You are not permitted to leave until <<1>> is done with you.
How is your project coming along?
I am eager to see what you're making.
How's the work going?
Shoo, shoo. Away with you! The beetle's mine - what's done is done. Your part is through, now move along!
Perhaps the Kagesh were right after all. Perhaps we should have simply prayed harder.
Hello, my love, my sweet birthday surprise.nnThere's just one other thing I want from you now ....
Whether you pray to the gods or not, I hope they're watching over you.
They say there's a lich commanding an army of Daedra atop Gil-Var-Delle.nnI say we kill it.
The spirits of this place will never forget you, <<1>>.nnLet me know if you'd like me to teleport you back to the surface.
A battle is in progress. I must observe.
He left me. He left me for the marshes.nnIt is fair. I abandoned him first.nnMaybe we will meet again, before we both feed the roots of a tree.
I need to you to bring me some raw garnet from the hills south of Davon's Watch. nnI'll show you the marvels that sleep inside a simple stone.
You've identified the right flowers.nnYou've properly extracted their oil. nnWell done!
These hides are crude, but they'll do.
I trust that wasn't difficult!nnLet's see what you've found.
We've spread word of your deeds under sun and sky. You'll be welcome in the village of the Kagesh now.
Several of our injured wardens are suffering because they're so close to Gil-Var-Delle. nnPlease tell me you've brought our rings back.
You've done more than enough, <<1>>.nnI'd head back to the Pilgrimage, if you haven't gone there already. They have their own problems.nnIn fact, some of their problems are worse than ours....
Did you free them...? Did you free the prisoners?nnYou... can't let Calypsi get near them.
Arafal disappoints me. I should have known.nnNow you are left to clean up her mess. I wish there were more I could do to help, myself.
You look a little singed, my friend. I think you've been playing with firelings!
You live! The Prince carried you out... I feared the Dominion lost its champion.nnThis is a sign. When death cannot claim the strongest among us, we will charge boldly to victory!
He got what was coming to him.
Without your perseverence, and without Gurles' sacrifice, the princess would have been lost to us. Now she is back... given new life. I pray this strange woods magic may keep her from future harm.
Laughing would be disrespectful.
You chose well in not choosing me. I'm sure your choice of Regent will prove most beneficial to Evermore.
Hmm. I cannot say I approve of your choice, but it is done.
A thousand words of praise upon you, <<1>>.nnThe saltrice you brought will sustain us for days.
Climb vines to reach the mushroom tops. nnWe use the vines to hide and quickly move through the forest. They help with our defense of Karthdar.
If you wouldn't mind helping, talk to <<1>> north of here along the road. nnShe's doing her best to keep Karthdar running, even in this time of crisis.
You have the amulets? nnWhat did you have to exchange? Wait, no. I don't think I want to know.nnGet those amulets to Tyr, and may Arkay watch over you.
You found the body of a goatherd?nnSo the stories are true!nnThe minions of the Withered Hand are tearing at us from all sides.
Thank you for helping us.nnYou're a good person.
Goblins! Such despicable beasts. nnThey have no appreciation for history whatsoever.
It's a shame the rioting had to end so soon. nnThe clatter of swords, the crash of broken glass, the roar of angry drunks... it's enough to bring a salty tear to this old sailor's eye.
I will assert my considerable influence over the stuttering dock workers and calm them.
You wouldn't dare tell my crew I'm losing my eyesight. nnI'll have you know my eyes are well-accustomed to the ocean. nnThings just don't look the same when we're not at ea.
I expect the beetles to clear out soon and then we can get back to work.nnI'm never overjoyed to get back to work, but I am grateful to fulfill my father's dying wish.
Stay clear of the docks.nnThe workers have risen in a violent riot.
How do you fare, <<1>>? nnAre we finished here?
Now that we've completed the repairs, we need more laborers to work the rain catchers, or we'll fall behind on Sentinel's demands for water.
Word has reached me of what happened at the seraglio. I should have seen this coming.nnPlease. Tell me you found Prince Azah and he is safe.
My Abuhir was my light, my life. What will we do now?
Since you left, the king has doubled our patrols. This is progress.nnThank you for helping Ilmaha and his family. They are dear friends.
This place is such a mess. I'm it's going to take hours to clean it all up.
Thank you for meeting me.
Those thugs took my father!
Stormhold is in your debt, <<1>>. You will always be welcome here.
By the bloody fangs of Mauloch! By the stench of Mauloch's gaping maw!nnWhat have you done? How can this be? I'm  free?
You must get the sabotage plans before the Withered Hand courier does. Look for a crate on the small dock to the northwest.nnHurry!
Tell Bahir to order all ships to stay in port. I must inspect them before they depart.

HeyI know you! We killed that crazy old necromancer togetherAngof. Remember the midnight talisman we used to break into Cath Bedraud? I still can't believe that worked. nnSo I don't suppose you need help with something fun like that?
You're amazing, <<1>>.nnI hope to one day be half the hero you are.
Is it true the Flu died out years ago? Is it true we can go outside again?
Is it true the Flu died out years ago? Is it true we can go outside again?
Is it true the Flu died out years ago? Is it true we can go outside again?
My father's of a better nature than he appears by speech. Pay no mind to his grumblings.nnIt's not you, in truth. It's my Devad. He disapproves of my match.

No need to be picky with the guar steaks. The cheapest cuts will do in the short term. Like they say about wine - you don't start with the finest vintage. An unschooled tongue can't appreciate the subtleties.nnI'll just need to check for maggots.
May the shadows comfort you, and if Sithis wills, you find peace in its embrace.
You are welcome among us, though we do not know you as brother. We will aid you if the Nest-Mother wills it.
Yes. I believe Bergama is where you should begin your search for the other two Ansei Wards.nnI will keep the Ward of Ansei Radan for now, but I will return it to you when you are ready.
Thanks for helping <<1>>.
Did you find a <<1>> yet?
This sewer was a dangerous place even before the Fervor. Crazy you yourself must be, for wandering into the lair of the Pellingare gang.
Please, I can't go to prison. You have my word I won't steal again, if you just show mercy this once!
Don't worry about me.nnOnce you find <<1>> in the sewers and reveal him for the traitor he is, the city guard will have to release me!
I can taste my child's blood upon you. He did not wish to discuss his decision to betray me, I take it?
Whatever you learned from the spirits, take it to Telenger. I've no time for you right now.
I mourn for my fallen brother, but if he betrayed the trust of the Nest-Mother, it is better he serve to feed the worms.
I know what you're going to say, child.nnMy apologies, that was not meant as a jest. Go on. Speak of what you've seen.
