The Nest-Mother guides our might and will with the blessing of Sithis. To turn away from his command is to invite catastrophe.nnWhat honeyed words is this Prophet spouting?
What do they want with us?
I do not like the looks of this....
More spirits? I thought you were leading us to safety.
Never can have enough dead monkeys, you ask me.
This is a disaster - the spirits refuse to let us leave in peace! Please, <<1>>, speak with them.
I heard the Shadowscale emblem was a fake. Whoever wants to mess with them must be crazy.
Does it really matter whether the Gods acted themselves, or if they inspired Ayvas to act?nnThe gods have shown him our doom.
Is it true what my people told me? Is that man out on the rocks a liar?

This village will die. One by one, these people will be broken by debt. They will be sold to mines, plantations, bordellos.nnWe are not ready for the outside world. We've lived too purely to endure its temptations.
<The spirit stares right through you.>
That journal you carry, it looks familiar.... But such things are unimportant.  Have you tasted this wine?
My mind no longer swims and my eyes are no longer covered.  Is it over?
Thank you stranger! I'd go myself, but the streets aren't safe! nnKids keep trying to grab me, and one man tied me up and made me dance! Then he even took all the money!
Unishi is pleased to see you again. You have made the deliveries to this one's clients, yes?
It seems it is my day to rejoin the One. If the Nest-Mother wills it, I shall.
<<1>> quickly spread the news about the Shadowscales' innocence. Frankly, I'm not sure which I'd rather deal with more, Shadowscales, or necromancers.
I can't believe you destroyed the Omen of Time's Passage. Well done!
The old trading post was to the southwest, along the Oortrel River. It was called Ten-Maur-Wolk.
Keep your wits about you. The unwary often find themselves chained in Alten Corimont.
Walks-in-Shade took too long in sending someone, I only hope the Archein loyalists are still there.
You're back. Alive, even. That's enough to be proud of.nnWhy risk your life trying to achieve the impossible?
<<1>> should be happy we're only keeping him in a guarded room in the lower floor of the Town Hall. He would have ended up in a nice gloomy cell if it were up to me.
It looks like you had no problems getting the job done. Thank you for offering your assistance. I just have one more favor to ask of you, if you have the time.
It was good of you to help Rinlan.nnI certainly wasn't going to help him.nnAll that talk about consecrated dead... leave it to the priests, I say.
And you would be...?

I obtained the idol at great risk to my person. It is, perhaps, the most important piece of ancient history I have recovered so far from the swamp.nnThe Archein savages will probably use it as a paperweight. I cannot stand the thought!
You're <<1>>, aren't you?nnI've been awaiting your arrival.
If one more thief robs me today, I'm going to stab him over and over until he's dead.
Marimah is lost. Never again will the sun cast his shadow beside mine.nnThere is nothing for me among the Ash'abah now. Alik'r is calling to me.
Sep's fangs! Marimah was suffering from the poison the entire time! nnWere you able to cleanse the poison from the johad wells? At least that would be a victory for the tribe.
You could say the Naga attack has... "burned out." Yes?nnHst. I just don't understand the humor of other races.
I can feel my lungs filling with fresh air again!nnThat yellow fog that was clogging my breath is finally dispersing.
The fresh ones are detained to the west, Dark One. The soul gems are here in the camp. I am sure you will be pleased.
We must breach Tu'whacca's sanctum and stop Uwafa.

To think her guardians laid dormant all this time. You have done what I thought never to see. But our work is not yet done, for the despoilers still lie within her.nnThe guardians will protect you, <<1>>. Enter her demesne and strike them down.
Ah! There you are. The Ash'abah who was with you just returned, saying you had become separated.
Thank you for cleansing our johads.nnThe water may taste strange, but at least it will not kill us!
Hopefully, <<1>> won't be too upset with the news.
That's all of them.nnYou were kind to help a stranger in the desert. Thank you.nnMay your throat never dry.
The spirit has been saved, but your countenance is grim.nnWhat happened?
I'll see what I can do to pick up Alasan's trail. nnIn the meantime, you should ask around Bergama about him. Perhaps Justice Istah knows more.
I hope the aberrations don't give you too much trouble.
The Hist must be protected as she protects us. Were you successful?
You have taught the Blood Cult a lesson, no?
My men are finishing off the last of the mercenaries. Hopefully, they won't be back.
I'm not sure how you survived, but next time you won't be so lucky.
I saw you speaking with Keethius. What happened?
Who was the handsome man who just came storming out of here?nnThat was not our culprit, was it?nnA shame if so. I would of much liked to handle that one myself.
I hope he accepts my offer. I'm pretty sure their Cult is just east of here.
Only someone with your experience can train our more senior members.
I don't have the nerve to try to escape. I'd rather live as a slave. Go on without me.
You've found J'Derr, yes? Dar'Virr can't bear to leave port without his raven.
I supported you all along.  Now that you're in charge, we'll be unbeatable!
Find Inerri and kill her. Cut off the head and the body will die. The Cult of Sangiin deserves to suffer for killing my men!
Were you able to retrieve many remains?
You will lead us to a properous future, <<1>>. I know it.
I can hardly believe this is real. So much has transpired.... Forgive me, dear friend, I am overwhelmed with emotion.
We should not have left her behind. Lorkhan's breath! There had to be another way....
Telenger appears quite adversely affected by today's events. Why don't you speak with him? I believe it would provide him some degree of comfort.
Please, Ahmuzi encourages you to go speak to <<1>>.nnYou should be able to find him in the military quarters to the east. This one is sure he will find a good use for you.
I feared as much as soon as Fargoth failed to show up. Poor Fargoth. I'll miss him.nnThank you for looking in on him for me. At least now I know.
With Dredis dead, perhaps we can sway the minds of the remaining mercenaries. Report to <<1>> back in Stillrise. We'll finish up here.
We were lucky to have you discover our small village here. Thanks to you, we can look to our new lives in peace.
You have my thanks! I wouldn't have escaped without you.
I couldn't wait any longer. Did you find the pair?nnI don't need their ghosts haunting my mine along with all these spiders!
Did someone send you to help? It's awful! My fellows have gone mad!
Ghassaj has seen you interrogating the dirty ones around here.nnThis one wonders what you may have learned?

So my own people have been taking the villagers of Velyn Harbor, eh?nnMa'Zarman does not like this! If only I could convince Larland that we should kill these traitors.nnBut, no pay for us, no killy killy for them.
Prince Azah has been anxiously awaiting your return. You should speak to him right away.
You were wise to support me, <<1>>. I will lead us to prosperity.
Thank you for saving me. Venosir is too wounded to travel on his own.
Thanks, <<1>>. Who knows how long before they found no use for me and let my blood water the trees.
Move along. Do not crowd the entrance.
Why did you not tell me you were a slave? I would see you whipped for wasting my time, but I will leave that to your master.
I feared that after all these years, my sacrifice would prove to be of no avail, but you performed admirably. nnWe cannot kill that necromancer, but he will trouble us no more.
That bottle you hold... is it the elixir for my son?nnIt smells rather oddly, but I shall not complain.
<<1>>! Thank the winds they have not found you. The others are gone - taken by the Archeins. I fear the worst.

I would advise you to use the utmost caution.nnThose woods are dangerous. All types of beasts and savages roam about, ready to tear at anything that would come near it.nnYou will find Murkvale just to the east. Be swift, <<1>>.
Lei-Kai must trust you if he sent you here. Doesn't mean I do, but I'll give you the benefit of the doubt.
The Minister is waiting on you. I would not make such a man impatient through tardiness.
My children hunger. Until you appease them, we have nothing to discuss.
I'm not sure joining this cult was the best idea. I've never even swung a weapon before and there is talk of us resisting both the Wardens and the Archein?
Shiri will avenge my death and the injustices of a callous king.nnThe Withered Hand will march over all of Alik'r, and our power shall darken the sky!
Help the scouts stave off the werewolf attack. If they die, we won't survive the night.
Guard my back. If we die, there's no one left to defend the townsfolk.

By the holy light, out of the entire guard you pick her?nnWell done, my friend! She refused to even speak to me earlier in the day. You would be surprised by her reaction when told her I had healing hands. Let's hope she doesn't ask about that again.
Whatever you can find will help us a great deal. You might even see if the bandits are carrying any things we can use.
I can't thank you enough for your help. If you hadn't come along, they'd still be trapped or worse eaten for dinner.
We'll remember what you did here for us.
Are you ready for your next lesson?

You'll have to search the town to find them all. The attack came so suddenly, I didn't have time to look for my friends. Now they're something else... something monstrous. I can't bear to see them like that!
Please, get me out of here!
This is great! It's perfect.nnI think we'll have a hit on our hands.nnHow fast can you run by the way?
Every mer who yet lives owes their life to you, <<1>>. I don't suppose I have to tell you how much they appreciate it.
I brought a bunch of miners from Wayrest with me. I'm the only one who escaped those spiders.nnWhat will I tell their families?
I have urgent news, <<1>>. <<2>> now leads the Cult of the Fang. You are to be exiled, despite all you've done for us.
Thanks for the delivery.
Please, don't hurt me. I've told you everything I know!

The only way to <<1>> is through the cave before us. Be careful. The Hand is using undead from their army as sentinels.nnHopefully, <<2>> won't be hard to find. I refuse to leave his fate in the hands of those necromancers.
We shall remain watchful on Starvale's borders. No more shall invaders tread upon Valenwood's soil so harshly.

The gaoler loiters about the docks when not on duty. It is just across the way from here.nnI am not worried about our friend telling the Archeins anything of import. I fear they may tire of their fruitless questions, and be done with him.
Warmblood, I have felt the pain of the Hist deep within me, and I know that the Hist has been harmed. Did you make them pay for their crimes?
The lair's entry is concealed. Let me clear it for you.nnHe will be inside. Your strength is greater than mine. Let us hope it is also greater than his.
I suspected the Ansei would speak to you. You are unlike any student we have seen for a very long time.nnI believe you will save Alik'r from the Withered Hand.
Ah, there you are, <<1>>.
Outsider, the Hunters have seen fewer Lost ones lurking in the swamps. Have you killed many?
I do not know that the old master deserved death. We could've saved her, benefited from her experience.nnBut I'm sure <<1>> will do her best to fill the void.
You have fought well today.
You have dueled admirably today.
You have seen how a proper defense enhances a deadly attack.nnI hope the lesson serves you well.
If you are not trained to avoid or weather a two-handed strike, it can devastate you.nnToday, you have gained respect for the two-handed style and learned to counter it effectively.
I'm pretty sure my dishes have wandered north. Or perhaps it's saucered north. They went right through this window!
What has the river washed ashore?
You're the one who walked into Ten-Maur-Wolk and killed the Nagas' Tribe-Caller.nnIt's all so easy for you, isn't it? Do wamasu line up to fall on your weapons?

You killed the Tribe-Caller, yes? I tell the younger warriors that entering an enemy camp is like diving into water. It will only break you if you're intent on making a splash.nnPerhaps your example will make them think a bit more.

<<1>> hasn't been well since the madness started. Maybe he has the madness too. Wouldn't that be a pity? He and I kept everyone together. Now I have my hands full here.nnHis hut is just to the east. The largest in the village.
Did you speak to <<1>>?
Is it done? Have you put my husband out of his misery?
It seems our actions did not go unnoticed.
I understand you're responsible for the new equipment we have. It's been a long while since I was able to properly maintain my armor.
Were you successful? The lights appear fewer, but I must be sure it's not another trick to deceive me.

You must hurry! His ritual will shatter one of the Ansei Wards and lower Alik'r's defenses against necromancy. nnIf <<1>> succeeds, every corpse in <<2>> will rise from the grave. My people will be in terrible danger!
You do us a great honor by being a part of this hatching. Do you have questions?
Are you here for a beating? We can oblige.
I can hear the roar of what sounds like fire nearby. I hope that you've brought good news.
It worked! I told you! Now, can someone please see about letting me go?

I saw few orcs try to escape. You must have been quite effective.nnI should have had you clean up the fleeing orcs - my vengeance does not feel sated. Tell me of your successes, I will have to be satisfied with that.
The potion will only work in the radius of the Spider Daedra's nest  Be careful around the mouth of the cave, as it may wear off there.nnTell Lucan what I mentioned.
So, you are the one the others spoke of so highly.nn<<1>> has brought shame upon Leki's Blade. I would hear your thoughts before adding my own.
There's more to this than simple piracy.

You've found them? You are a master thief, my friend! I could never have done this as quickly as you.nnCould... could I ask you to deliver these to my master? He lies in the house next to me. I fear he may be... cross.
I am glad Master Fadalia accepted you.nnMay the Eight keep you safe.

I wouldn't normally ask a stranger to help, but you look like you can handle yourself better than most. And, if you do manage to find something, <<1>> won't hesitate to reward you for your help. He's hiding on the island at the bottom of the basin.
If you're going to stick around, the least you could do is help.nnSpeak to Kasal. He owns the place, and I work for him.
I'm sorry to hear what happened at the mines.nnI hope they get it all cleaned up soon.
My offer still stands, if you find yourself on the wrong side of the law. What is five years of work for ensured safety?
Have you done it? Nothing is left of Amorline in this place?
Well? What are you looking at? Expecting me to go haunt something? Begone!
You should hurry to HoonDing's Watch. Whatever Thahala wants to speak with you about seemed urgent.
Hmph. It seems you've been able to conjure the greatest illusion of all, <<1>>. Hope.
Thanks to you, the Withered Hand now has one less necromancer to increase its forces.nnI must reconvene with <<1>>. May Tall Papa always watch over you, friend.
With you leading us, we will become an unbeatable force!
Hopefully your rule will be longer than Keethius'.
It is a terrible thing to destroy the sap of a Hist. But it would be worse to let Imperials and cultists have it.nnThey are unworthy of its blessings.
These things your returned will fetch quite a price. Good work.
Her hair was like the waterfalls at Silvenar. Her skin was pale as the moon. Oh, my sweet Amorline!
We heard quite a ruckus up there seems you've been causing some problems for them. Good!
You should be able to find the bandits near any of the graht-houses throughout Murkvale. Good hunting, <<1>>.
Take the bones from the Withered Hand, then meet me in the desert north of here. I will arrange a way for us to dispose of them.
You found Cerelas! Please, keep looking for the others. They must be out there!

Gather the runes and return to place them upon their proper altars.nnThe spirits of scholars who once accompanied me will aid you in their placement.nnBe warned. Placing the relics on the wrong pedestal will only bring pain and punishment.
My apologies. My fellow guards have informed that you're an actual living being.

The ones you will encounter were my friends. My companions. But it has been far too long since we have been here. They have drifted into madness and lost their way.nnRelease them and the relic's purpose will be known.
That was exciting.nnUgh. You'd better take a step back. I think I'm going to be sick again.
I'm glad to see you made it here safely, friend.
Have you come seeking knowledge at <<1>>?nnThe swordsmen here are the best in all the Redguard kingdoms.
She chose me? Oh fortuitous day,
Shamar and I will see each other soon. I am sure we will have quite an adventure together.
So she has made her choice? There can be only one result.
The wood orcs have done so much damage to our farms. I fear it will take years to recover, especially with how many of us were slain in their brutal attack.
Guess I need to find myself a new occupation. You couldn't pay me to go back into those blasted tunnels.
Fancy seeing you here! It's good to see you again, <<1>>, I was starting to miss you.nnHow's the being-a-hero working out for you?
Your help has been greatly appreciated, <<1>>. My life is extended for another few years thanks to you.
You have doomed us to several more years of servitude.
What? I'm a Dominion soldier, I freed myself. It's not like we're not used to dealing with wood orcs, although it's surprising that they'd dare to attack here.
What happened at the Magistrate's House? Do you find evidence that she's involved in the disappearances?
The rite is held near the hatching pools to the southeast. It is under the weeping tree.nnBring the venom and present it as your offering. You will be welcome.
Four eggs. Good job, my friend. nnNow I need your help deciding what to do next.

They say lying in the sun is the best thing for a cold. Or was that food? Food for a cold?nnNo, wait. It was starving for fevers. You gather moss for a cold, and soak your gills for lampreys. No?nnWait, I'll get this.
<<1>>, you have proven yourself a cunning hunter and gifted slayer. You do the <<2>> people proud.
Ugh. Mrgh.
I am going to make my way to Silvenar to find more help. We were unprepared for the dangers of this place.
Thank you for bringing the dryad's gift to me. We will - I mean I will - always be grateful to you.
So you delivered the sapling to Gatheron's son. It will bring him much comfort, I am sure
The others are getting something out of this that I'm not.
You could just talk directly to me, you know. I am standing right here.
Tall Papa as my witness, Fakimal's murderers will pay for their crime in blood.
I can't believe Fakimal was murdered! I've known him since he was a boy.nnWho would do such an awful thing?
Poor Fakimal. He never ordered anything but water, but he always tipped well.nnHe was a good man. He didn't deserve what happened to him.

It's been quiet here. You'd think, so many visitors, it wouldn't be.nnThe most noise I've heard in the last week was the night those pirates broke out the flin. Drunken sea-chanties all night.nnOr would those be river-chanties here?
I know it is cowardly for me to allow this to continue until it affected me so. But for Riane, I would risk my life.
The dead boar is wearing a decorative collar. Faded symbols adorn the fur. Its throat is slit, and a bowl beneath it is encrusted with dried blood.
I plan to return to Mournhold as soon as possible. I doubt my family will take me in after running away with an Argonian, but living on the streets there is better than living in finery in the muck.
Dead things that come to live again taste bad. Crawl about in the belly. Hmm. Yes.
My heart cannot rest easy until I know the Lion Guard have been saved.
You've made a real difference in our lives here. We can't thank you enough.
Hurry. Talk to Kabrahla. Cleanse Lainlyn.nnA chill is spreading through me quickly. I don't want to become a zombie.
The flames have taken on a ghostly, blue-white hue with the addition of the ritual ingredients.
You chose your path, trading with Idrasin. He may have been fair to you, but he is a curse to the poor here. Keep your distance from us - you are no longer favored.
What treasures do you have so far? You can find all manner of things down in the sinkhole - surely an adventurer like yourself is not afraid of the creatures there!
You mentioned finding a note?
I have waited so long for your return. I feared the worst for you. I don't suppose you succeeded in such an impossible task...
The best way for us to survive is for the Archeins and Wardens to destroy eachother.

<The last entry reads:>nn"My mother fell ill today. I'm terrified, but she thinks she found a ritual to protect the rest of us.nn"Those of us who are healthy have been told to go to the shrine and pray."
I am pleased to have been able to contribute so significantly and so noticably to Telenger's research.nnYou were a valuable part of the process as well, <<1>>. For that I thank you.
I never imagined I could be this happy.
My eyes can see the evidence of your deeds all around me. Your time in the desert sands was well spent!
You... you did it.nnThe Tear... take it. It is yours now.nnYou must save the forest.

In the sand, beetles! Behind the rocks, beetles! Around the johads, beetles! Last night, I woke up and one was in my tent, just just watching me!nnWe can't do our work! Sentinel's going to run out of water!
I'm glad someone's taking care of things.nnYou're a rare sort, wayfarer.
I cannot thank you enough for telling me what you found. Even though it was not the news I had hoped for.
This isn't how I thought I'd spend my retirement.
"Go to the Strand," they said. "Relax. Enjoy the fresh air."nnPfaugh.
If we do not get the spine cactus cuttings soon I fear this brave soldier will surely die.

We wouldn't want to limit your fun, now would we?nnWhy don't you try for some more vouchers? Three tokens is all you need. Three tokens and another prize voucher is yours!nnMore games for you! More games!
Justice Istah is in the stocks just over there.nnGo speak with him. Show him we know of his guilt!
<<1>>! You must know I did not murder Inila or Fakimal.
You brought me good things. Unless you have more things, we're done talking.
Hurry, <<1>>. The Silvenar Prime might not have much time left, if he is even still alive beneath all of these brambles.
We'll be cleaning up the Cult soon enough.nnSafe travels.
I got here as quickly as I could once the necromancer was occupied. It seems you dispatched him yourself with ease.nnDid you discover anything of note?
What did the spirit say? Do you know where <<1>> is hiding?

Between the two of us, I think Telenger should dismiss Meliara. She clearly offers little to his research and spends far too much time with her head in the clouds.nn"Divination", she calls it. I suspect laziness and distraction.
Don't just look at me with questioning eyes. If you have something to ask, just ask!
We have reason to rejoice, it seems!
Speak softly. Relazar's followers don't yet know what we've done.
I'm still shaking from all of this, but I have to look after Venosir now.

Have you destroyed them all? If the Withered Hand holds even one of these dogs in their thrall they will be able to grow these criminals into dark slaves of enormous power! You must act now while they are still weak and new to this unlife!
By the Long Tail, you have the look of righteousness about you! How fared you?
Don't just stand there! The lamiae hatchlings are coming to eat me!
<<1>> better come through on his promises. My associates are not amused by his delays.
Satakalaam is overrun with Withered Hand and their undead minions. But there are still survivors. We cannot in good conscience ignore their plight.

Be sure to let Ma'Zarman know this is of the utmost importance. Many lives are at stake here, I fear. There is a dark magic at work to be sure.nnIf I have judged him as I judged you, he will help us. He is a good man underneath all that... fur.

Hey, don't pester me anymore; you got all that you're going to get out of me.nnWord of advice though, stranger. Valaydia doesn't like people asking questions around here. You might want to remember that.
Have you the materials we need?
The arrogance of the Worm Cult will be their undoing.
target: The arrogance del Culto del Verme will be their undoing.

source: If the caste leaders had known what the Cult was doing with these pirates, they'd never have agreed to work with them.

In our fight against the Nedes, we saw the raw power of defiance. We came to respect Tamriel and its warriors. nnYou must now battle the giant goblinkin. The Ra Gada's long road to conquest was paved with thousands of these beasts' corpses.
Thank Ruptga! You've found them! Those eggs brought me nothing but worry. I don't want anything more to do with them.nnPlease, take them to Daneem. He promised me he'd deal with this.
I saw my men running to freedom. Thank you. Even the lowliest pirate donesn't deserve such a fate.
Ah-hah! M'adric knew you could do it.nnWas not hard, was it?
Thank you for aiding my Captain and my comrades. I'm sure they'll be along soon to find me.

Extinguish the watch fires and the dreugh should renew their attack on Bleaker Rock. Be careful, the Maormer have guards posted around each fire.nnWhen you're done meet me near the crates in the Bleaker Rock camp.

You can light the torch at any of the fires spread around Bleaker Rock. Watch your back. They'll probably have guards posted around the fires.nnBurn the rowboats and meet me by the Captain's tent near the beach when you're finished.
I heard you are the one responsible for returning our memories. Why would you do that? We all came here willingly. We wanted to forget!
Don't tell me you're scared of a few snakes. Just put the urn over their head and scoop them in! Preferably before they bite you.
You think he'll forgive me, right?
I have... a few breaths left. Let me give you what knowledge I have, if it will aid you in destroying the Worm Cult and their Children of Sithis.
This forest cries out in anguish and rage. Y'ffre needs us now, just as we have always needed him.
I heard you've been trying to find a villager who went missing. Since you helped me, I'll give you some advice. You should abandon your investigation. Some things happen for a reason.

Our meeting was not one of chance. It was of my choosing.nnMy people must feed. They must survive. But only the strong, smart, and cunning wet our appetites.nnYou have proven you are worth such an honor.
Your work here is done, mortal friend. Both you and Dan-Shei have earned my gratitude.nnDid you wish my aid escaping this cavern?
I saw my men running to freedom. Thank you. Even the lowliest pirate donesn't deserve such a fate.
I think we'll leave this place soon. Now that you've rescued Hram perhaps it's time to find another god to worship .

Collect the other three map pieces. Kill the First Mate and collect his piece, find Captain Gromiar's map piece in the wreckage of the Sea Trawler, and recover the piece from Captain Ravenil on the island just offshore.
Is... is she dead?
Here he is, sister! The one who saved me from being devoured by ravenous lamiae. nnI still can hardly believe I escaped. I was certain they were going to eat my bones!
Did you see it? I've never seen a troll so big.
The fog is being lifted. My memory is slowly returning.
You've done good work. Better than Harus ever did.
Of all things, the Sergeant is here! I don't know why please go and speak to him. He can't find out I paid you to do my work!
Be safe exploring HoonDing's Watch.
All have been warned of the hatching, <<1>>? You have made yourself part of the sharxal?

Ma'Zarman will find you back at the game tents when you are done.nnIf there are any more innocents in the area, this one will get them to safety. Would not want them to be turned into the blood in the crates, no?
I hear that you are being honored by the elder. nnYou are one of them, and you are strong. Perhaps I should be learning from you.
Congratulations, <<1>>. An Argonian always gets this honor, but they usually choose from other Keepers of the Shell. It is rare that someone outside gets to spread the sharxal.
This is horrible! nnThe weapons of the Ansei have been safe in Sentinel for generations. Now they're gone!

You did not have the right to interfere with our affairs. People came here to forget. They did this willingly. nnYou have forced them to face a past they had tried to leave behind. You should leave this place. Now.
How goes your work? Are the snakes giving you too much trouble?
Take our message to <<1>> quickly.nnI fear for my brothers and sisters of the Ash'abah. The Withered Hand is a terrible enemy.

You will find several drinks on the table.nn<<1>>, a beverage that is not as potent at the others but takes a bit to drink.nn<<2>>, which goes down with ease but packs a punch.nnAnd <<3>> to help clear up any sickness you might feel from all of this.
You saved me! One day, I will walk in peace on the distant shores of Tu'whacca's realm, but that day is not today.nnI am still worried about the other Ansei.
Go on. I will just turn myself in. I suppose this will exonerate Istah. You should speak to him.
I'll do what I must to save <<1>>. But, maybe there's another way besides being covered in spiders again .
Our leaders welcome guests. You may speak to them if you wish.nnPlease do not disturb the eggs.
Report your findings about <<1>> to <<2>>.nnHe'll want to know how this ended.
You have delivered the warning to Sunscale Strand? Good.
The Worms are relying on our sentries to keep them safe. They betray us, yet rely on our loyalty to protect themselves.nnFools. We do Tamriel a favor by removing them.
I understand what <<1>> wants, but I don't want Black Marsh to turn into a copy of Cyrodiil. I want it to remain Black Marsh.nnWell. So long as we get the Pact out, we can discuss the rest later.
At least once a week, the Worm Cult makes dinner for us all. I don't know what it is, but it's delicious.nnThe Cult is very considerate. Respectful. We made the right choice in allying with them.
Ancestors guide you, <<1>>. Stormhaven boils over with troubles; only sure feet and strong purpose will deliver you safely to <<2>>.
Go through the gate here. The pit is to the north and west.nnDon't worry about the Worm Cult guards. They like to watch people in the pit - they get bored too.
These ruins are far more dangerous now then when I was a child. These old claws would do no good in a brawl.nnI will wait to give you a head start, then follow in your wake.
I had not thought to see these words again. Our... history is lost to every living being, but here, you have found a fragment of who we once were.
The skull has been in our village for many seasons. We did not think of where it might have come from.nnWho knew that Zud-Reen held the secret all this time?
Hurry up and get that bucket of water and put out those fires! I have to wait here and stall The Thane if he comes to investigate!
<<1>> can be found within the great temple of Wayrest. It's in the city's southwest corner.
Thank you for killing that goblin!

This note, the missing priests, the foretelling of a murdered moth  it can't all be coincidence.nnI know it sounds crazy, but will you do as the letter says? I fear if I went myself, I would only end in the same trouble as my missing brethren.
<There is little left of this tablet. The stone has been worn away by weather and time. A few letters remain clear, despite its condition.>
You've robbed these people of their second chance. We had built something great here and you've ruined it.
The focus crystals, have they been returned to the Spinners?

I see you've gathered the shards. That's good.nnThere were... awful noises out there. I don't want to know what the effects of the extraction were.nnYou have what you came for. Go find my fellow Spinner to get his crystals as well.
We heard some fighting going on. Everything all right?
Good work with the investigation. Let's hope it doesn't happen again.

Take great care when placing the urns. You should place them in locations that the average scout will not see them. That will make their magic more effective.nnIf any of the scouts stares too long in the direction of any urn the magic will be broken.
What could be keeping <<1>>?
Did you... you killed him? Y'ffre's bark, you killed him!
Don't let it kill me!

I thought I'd try one of these "fishing poles" the Dunmer use. So far I haven't caught a thing.nnI think I'll go back to our traditional method - sit on the river bed and don't move until a fish swims up to your jaws.

In the dying days of the Maruhkati Selective, those madman shut themselves away in an underground fortress.nnBut their enemies found them there. The foes fought their way in. Time passed. None emerged. It was their final refuge.

What The Huntress is doing here shakes me to my very core. I can't believe that I was fooled by her posturing for so long!nnMy soul is in anguish for the innocents that suffered under my hand when I served The Huntress!
I'll take care of cleaning this up here.nnGet to Mahnor and stop him before it's too late! If the Imperials are already there, they must all die. nnOtherwise my village will be slaughtered.
You have what you came here for.nnIt's too late though. You'll never get to them in time.
Are the altars all destroyed?
Are the altars all destroyed?nnI saw some flames in the distance and I thought it might be your work.
Did you do what I asked? Did you destroy the spirits?nnWe need to make sure to weaken The Huntress' army before we move against her.
I was here to see the book destroyed, that book you so foolishly gave to the Bosmer prince.nnWe have nothing more to discuss. Begone!

Once the mudcrab is in the water, just be patient.nnIf it starts to squirm, give the string a hard yank. Hopefully if anything is chasing it down there, it'll give it enough time to get out of its way and keep looking.
Add the sleep potion to the Midnight Union's drinking kegs. That should put the bandits to sleep. nnThen search the counting house. We need to know where they're keeping Miranda.

Our mages are investigating the tome and should have a plan of attack in short order. Thanks to you, we will soon be able to overrun and drive the Imperials from our forest!nnI admit, I had my worries, but victory now seems inevitable.
We're alive, after all that? I would not have thought it possible.nn<<1>>, I have never met one so heroic and brave as you. I surely would have been dead long before we reached this place.
Thanks, stranger. nnIf you find any survivors, tell them help will soon be on its way.
I have a terrible suspicion the Worm Cult is behind this. The thought of my fellow priests in the clutches of those death-worshippers makes me sick.

To wake up and realize the one you loved is gone will allow you to eventually heal in time. nnTo love one and know that it is damned and cannot succeed is a pain that is ever lingering.nnNow go. Get to my brother before he get's to Layliana.
You startled me, <<1>>. I heard someone coming and thought I had been discovered!
You should speak to Sister Kala. nnUntil she says move, I stay here.

Aww, look at how cute those two are.nnThere are many things in this world that are dark and vile, especially in these times. Sometimes the love of another is all we need to pull on through.nnDon't you agree?
Jemmaril always has something good to trade, even if it is just his usual gossip.

Not surprisingly, the Mages Guild of Wayrest is in the Mages District. nnFor a small fee, they'll send you to the Mages Guild in Shornhelm. That's in Rivenspire.nnOnce you arrive, find the local Ancestor Moth chapterhouse. Talk to the priests.
One day, the sun will shine on <<1>> and I as we walk the swamp.
<The embers are smouldering, yet they are cold to the touch. As you reach your hands toward the brazier, you hear a strange voice in your head, speaking in some foreign tongue.>
My grief awaits my love, have you spoken to her?
You will find the piles of bones throughout this place. Wherever you see the cult's unnatural minions, you will find the bones that spread their filth.
Hurry and free me! We must make haste!
I am less troubled now. I think the offering to Sithis was accepted.
Thank you. I feel much better already.
Collect the antidote to that poison before it's too late! nnLady Miranda's in the manor house. Use that key I gave you to get in.
Thank you for agreeing to return the welkynd stone to the temple. Hopefully, doing so will fill in the remaining holes in my memory.
Muzgu. Dead. nnI thought Azura would protect him. She didn't.
Honor and blood, my friend!  How goes the campaign?  I don't suppose you've slain any Daedroths yet, eh?  I could use a new pair of boots. Ha!
Find Sergeant Stegine. He's up the road in Dreughside.nnSo many dead.
I'll compensate the Dreughsiders. I'll leave, stay in Wayrest.nnPlease, just let me go free!
We heard everything. nnIs it true? Did Baron Sorick really plant the eggs?
Oh, the conversations I've been having!
Rumor has it there was a bit of a scuffle near the Mages Guild. Was that you?
What did you find? The crown of Emperor Reman?nnHeh. If I were that lucky, I wouldn't be digging through garbage.
Is it done? Have you made the cultists pay for their actions?
That was quite a downpour. I wonder what that was about?
It looks like all my boys are busy teaching other people a lesson. Come back when my men aren't engaged with other fools like you.
You want to fight? You sure about this?
I can't handle much more of this  hiding up here like some skeever.nnBut you've brought the book. Good. Give it to the old man.
The shouting of the rain tells me you completed the ritual. I am in your debt, <<1>>.
You amuse me. That's worth paying a pittance of a debt.nnNow take it and get off my dock.
Today, we heard your  performance. It was a glorious symphony of punishment!nnWe could hear it from here.
Praise Azura! You survived.
These ruins are far more dangerous now then when I was a child. These old claws would do no good in a brawl.nnI will wait to give you a head start, then follow in your wake.
At the end of every storm, a rainbow. Rajeren sees your clouded soul clearing up. What have you to tell Rajeren?
And here we are at last, <<1>>. Quite the adventure, yes?
Was it me, or did that cloudburst seem unusually warm?
Stew for all soon! Thank you, and may the waters be calm for you, <<1>>.

I... I don't know what's going to happen.nnAmyrlin... the Huntress... she's gone into madness. I believe Enerist is going to try and stop her once and for all, but....nnIs it right? Is what we're doing right?
Yes, yes. These things take time, <<1>>. This one will send word to Prince Aeradan when he has figured it out, yes?
I heard there was a ruckus down at the docks. They say someone chewed up the Grinder and spit him out.nnI'm guessing that someone was you.
I'm thankful that you came along. I thought for sure I'd never see my tomb urn again.
I watched you climb up to speak with <<1>>. What did he say?
I have heard that you also convinced <<1>> and <<2>> to give up the golden skull.nnYou should bring these tidings to <<3>>. He watches over the skull in the shrine at the center of town.
I have heard that you also convinced <<1>> and <<2>> to give up the golden skull.nnYou should bring these tidings to <<3>>. He watches over the skull in the shrine at the center of town.
With the Midnight Union affair cleaned up, we won't have to treat any more of their victims. nnNow that's something to look forward to.
How's your investigation going? Have you discovered anything new?
I have heard that you also convinced <<1>> and <<2>> to give up the golden skull.nnYou should bring these tidings to <<3>>. He watches over the skull in the shrine at the center of town.

If you develop your mind, you may one day possess the wisdom of a weaver.nnSadly, you will never possess our nimble claws. But we cannot all be born Argonian. Work with whatever gifts you've been given.
Are you sure I'm the one you wish to speak with?
If you have nothing to share but the stresses of the world beyond our swamp, it would be better for you to leave.
Our problems must seem insignificant to you. We have never gone beyond these marshes.
This one would speak with you for a moment, walker. nnYou might be interested in an opportunity to earn some gold by helping someone in need?
Azura go with you, friend. I hope her blessing might dispel the curse of Vaermina's cultists.
This is familiar. I remember you from Alcaire  the Vanne Farm! nnFunny we should end up surrounded by Supernal Dreamers again.
If the Worm Cult attack our village, we'll need many arrowheads.nnWe've been stockpiling them for so long... it's strange to think of using them.
I see that Rajeren still lives. Why does he still breathe, <<1>>?
Our victory here is nearly complete. Only one more thing stands between us and the elimination of our enemies.
I'm glad that's over. We need to get back to Camlorn.nnSee you around.
My wife is safe and welland my son came to me and apologized. nnYou are a wonder, and we're blessed to know you.
Unbeliever! You walk the path to righteousness, and it was I who showed you the way.nnMaruhk, forgive me!
We must trust in the gods. That's what I do. nnI've made many offerings to the Divines in these last dark days.
I gave you the shields. Tell Andre that I expect my cut of the profits tomorrow.
I'll be traveling back to Wayrest shortly. nnIf we see each other there, I don't know you.
<<1>> has a plan to use the lure. This day brightens.
I guess I'll never be done thanking you. nnI hate to imagine what would have happened if you hadn't defeated the Omen.
Something's different. I wonder what's going on? I don't like it.
The guards are looking rather anxious. Something's changed, hasn't it? And for the better. nnI think we might live through this.
We're going to be allowed to leave, aren't we? nnIt's over. I can tell.
Thanks for letting me know. Now report the tunnel collapse to Godrun down at the entrance to Shinji's Scarp.
The world of the living has trangressed. The energy of these relics was used for darkness. nnThe portal is closed, but something came through. It must be destroyed.
There is always danger in being a pirate, but how was <<1>> to know that it would be from one's own captain?
The ship is to the south. Save <<1>>, please!
Do you see? Do you see what I've become? Look at the reflection! nnI'm old. I'm fat. And sometimes Argonian! No one will ever admire me again!
I'm sorry. You'll simply have to excuse me. I'm getting to know myself and I'm not who I thought I was.nnYou can see it too. Just look. Look in the mirror.
You still here? nnJust tell that crazy Ashton I don't want any more of her worthless stones! nnDo you hear me?
Just passing through, traveler? I'm about to head out myself.
I hope to find new business soon or I'll have to relocte my shop.
What's the point of opening my mouth to speak?nnThere's nothing I can say to end this torment, so I'm just going to stop talking. I mean it.

I appreciate you doing this for me. My wife made me promise to get the refugees out of Crestshade and keep them safe, but I can't stop worrying about her.nnCrestshade is directly north of this camp and our house is right in the center of the town.
You can thank me for "losing" her soul gems.
The cultists who captured me must have trapped my father with the same enchanted sleep. They cast that same spell on me!nnOh, he must be suffering so much from the nightmares!
The Covenant thanks you for joining the war effort! With talented crafters like yourself at our back, there's no challenge we can't overcome.n nAkatosh bless your wares, friend.
Please  go away. They're going to see you!nnI'm not coming out until I see a head.
It does not surprise me that you have succeeded thus far, for you bear the Viridian Sentinel's favor. Now closing the portal is all that remains.
You should not delay, <<1>>. Drahir knows you want to kill just as much as he does.
What do you have there, <<1>>?
The Huntress has gone too far! This was a temple of innocents.nnWe could use your help, but I don't want to leave these monks unaided. Have you spoken to the Grand Master?
I'm busy. Leave off, vagrant. Find your own hole.
You know what amazes me? As muddy as these pigs get, they're still cleaner animals than the cows.nnYou know a cow will stand in its own waste for days. Won't even move unless you make it.
Was there some kind of incident up in front of the countess's manse?nnI've been trying to avoid that area lately. It simply reminds me of my failures.
I'm sorry. Am I not allowed to stand here? It's the countess's property, and she certainly hasn't said anything.nnSo yes, I'll just stay here as long as I like. Thanks!
A summons was recently sent ordering all Knights of the Flame to return to Firebrand Keep.nnFor now, though, I feel my duty is to remain here. Sir Hughes will understand.
Keep heading back to the north-east. You'll find our Treethane in the central most home.nnHe'll want to hear about how easily you stumbled upon this town.
These new mercenary guards have done wonders for my sense of security.
That poor soldier. He swore he would just scout the area and return immediately. He didn't intend to fight alone.nnI'll need to tell his family.
I cannot describe the sensation, even as a spirit, of being back in my father's presence.nnFate was cruel to us in life, but at long last, we've both found peace. Thank you.
You returnand I sense a diminishing of the evil 'round the tower. nnHow did you fare?
If this deal turns out to be a waste of my time, someone's going to pay for it.
Looks like you've got quite a load of raw ebony. <<1>> will be quite pleased with you, I imagine.
I'm acting on orders directly from Sir Hughes. If he wants to make an exception, he'll let me know in due time.nnUntil then, the envoy stays out!

Again, you must keep this quiet. The Duke is already overwhelmed and hearing about a spy inside the castle might push him over the edge.nnGet past Sir Gregory and into the library, find out who "Almandine" is, and report back to me personally.

I hope Baroness Edrald doesn't actually believe Arlie was dragged off to some Daedric plane.nnI've lived here a long while, and I've seen some strange things. But every time someone's child is "abducted by Daedra," it turns out they've eloped.
Together at last! Thank you, stranger. Now I beg you one final favor - a proper burial, as every decent person deserves.nnThe shrine is due north of here, at the entrance to the mine.
The ogres will double their numbers if you go against them with too many folks at once.nnI'm heading back. That's safer for both of us.
Yes! I smell them! Delicious, crispy, tasty, bloody. Scamp skins! Give!
If you die in this endeavor, we will not weep. Not for an outsider.nnSucceed, though, and my tribe will welcome you as clanfriend.

I hate to say it, but I'm going to have to speak with the duke about this. The fact that the duchess is sending secret letters to her father is serious cause for concern.nnWe need to know exactly what they're planning though.
It is a relief to see you returned. I fear I might have asked too much. nnTell me though, did General Thoda have any new insights into the source of these assassination attempts?
Still no sign of Mister Nurin? I told youhe's goneprobably burned up in the fire.nnMy heart goes out to the rest of the family, but I have to look out for myself. I'll have to find a new job!

I'm glad you came along. The constable's down by the docks. If he won't listen to reason, try to find the messenger from Alcaire Castle. He can explain everything.nnIf you can get me released, the Knights of the Flame will be in your debt.
So the crew of the Midnight Swell is innocent!  I'd hate to think Lucas fell prey to the slavers that attacked that ship.nnWhat does that mean for Koeglin Village? I hope Sal has a plan.
Fire, scamps, William disappears, and now strangers on the propertynnThe farmhands all gave up. Maybe I need to give up too. The farm's lost, and my sweet William
I gave the constable the message, but he doesn't seem to believe me.nnHe put Dame Dabienne in the stocks. Glad I'm not her!
Guards! Guards! Arrest these people!nnThey're setting up the village! The slavers are going to come back and take us all!nnWhy aren't you listening to me?
If his treatment of my crew had not been so disrespectful, I might feel a little sorry for the constable.nnAs it stands though, I'm quite enjoying this.
Were those Daedra death screams I heard? Music to my ears.nnAnd you destroyed those damnable portals too. I think now we'll be safe.
I can't tell you what a relief it is to learn that Pascal's mind is messed up.nnI guess that sounds a little strange, doesn't it?nnRegardless, I'm grateful for all your help.
Heard you were out there talking to that knight in the stocks. nnI'd be careful if I were you. Constable will lock you up too. Sit down and have a drink instead. What'll it be?
You did it. You even got him home in time for dinner.nnIt weighs heavily on a mother's heart to worry about her son. I can't thank you enough.
I'm with dad on this. I want to wipe every remnant, every trace of those sick freaks from our farm.nnIt's the only way we can start over.
I told you! I don't know anything. Go away!
As embarassing as my mother may be, it breaks my heart that she worries so much.nnIt's good that we've put her mind at ease. You should talk to her.
The Knights of the Flame are sworn to protect me and my family. How can I trust any of them now?nnFirebrand Keep is to the southeast. Go and bring Sir Hughes to justice. Let none stand in your way!
My daughter is back, thanks to you. nnShe seems none the worse for wear, though she's hesitant to talk about it. I have a feeling I'm better off not knowing.
So you're the one who destroyed that tunnel? Good work.nnThat'll give those filthy ogres something to think about!
Here we go again. I'll be hearing about this for yearshow I failed to save our son in his darkest hour, and oh, thank the Eight for that stranger .nnI guess it could be worse.

Well done! Frankly, I thought we'd be peeling you off the bottom of a rock, but hey, you made it!nnNow's our chance to drive the ogres back into the mountains. We can end this thing! I don't know why the general's hesitating!
If <<1>> wants to know about the battle, he should just come out and see for himself.nnWhat? Is he hiding or something?
Hm. You don't look so dangerous. Yet, you waltz into my camp and pick fights with my soldiers?nnTell me why I should not simply cut off your head where you stand?
You  you did it. nnAlready, I can feel peace coming over me. Soon, I will be  asleep.
Checking in on your old friend Manard again?nnHow  thorough of you.
You didn't really get ogre teeth for <<1>>, did you?
Of all the ports and over all the years, never a worse time and place to be stuck ashore.nnFifty crates of grain bound for Rihad, but right now, it's just rotting in the hold.
Sir Hughes decided to let that Redguard envoy in to speak with the Duke, and the soldiers went back to their camp.nnSo things are quiet here  for now.
They gobbled down my house key, those little devils. Cut them open until you find it.
Ma'jhad's so angry right now. Only the captain ever said those kinds of things about her. I'm afraid he's going to kill the first mate before she can escape.nnPlease, you've got to help her.
This is all wrong, all of it.nnThe sooner we find out who's responsible and restore the duchess, the better!
There are still others who need your help. Look for <<1>> near the town square. Help him, so he will be free to help us.nnOnce the defenders of Crestshade are assembled, we'll face the abomination.
Hey, you're not going into the warehouse, are you?nnConstable promised me that if anyone got to go in there and paint the walls with slaver blood it would be me.
Welcome back to the Hall, my friend.  Our librarians are anxious to pore over your discoveries!
It would be wise not to speak of this with anyone - especially not the members of House Indoril.nnWe both know what you did was right, but an outsider might question our judgement.
My husband, Sir Gregory, suddenly wants to take me to Wayrest. How very sweet of him!
Blackhearts dead! Dead!
Thanks for bringing me word about my sons. They're good hunters, almost as good as their sister.nnIt's a father's right to worry about his children, isn't it?
I'm sure my father's still worrying about me, but I'll be fine.nnNow that I know what to expect from these cats, they'll be dead soon enough.
Tell my father not to worry so much.nnRolan and I can handle ourselves in the wild just as well as Jehanna can.
Are the Dorrells looking? I bet they're looking.
I hope the Divines will watch over Shela and keep her safe. She's so brave.
Rumors sweep through <<1>> like the desert winds - they say the captain is slain, now and for all time!nnIs it so? You have done this thing?
The Duchess must be kept safe. I will stay here while you speak with Sir Hughes.nnI hope he will send additional security to protect her.
King Fahara'jhad will never forget the loss of his beloved Lakana, but I hope this man's death will bring him some sense of peace.
A crime was committed and the price had to be paid. I wish it could have been otherwise, but I have done my duty as you chose.

My husband's a little hard of hearing. Not quite in touch with reality either. He thinks he killed that scamp, but it was actually our cat.nnBless his heart though, he certainly means well. Just play along if you will.
Are there any more scamps down there? Bring them on, I say! 'Scampkiller' is my middle name! nnI can still wield a blade just like when I was a young man. Just watch!

Even if you speak the truth, I have no knights to spare. People plot against me in my own home. They're rioting, furious at my love for Lakana.nnI will protect her, and I will protect my people. You will leave it at that.
You've saved my husband. I can't tell you how grateful I am!
There was no luck in this, you know. I believe Stendarr sent you to us in our time of need.

Now that we're associates, allow me to introduce myself properly. I'm Count Hosni at-Tura. I'd like to invite you to my estate, where we will celebrate my betrothal.nnYou've whetted your appetite for blood. You know you want more. Join us, won't you?
You're alive!nnIt's true, then. <<1>> has finally been defeated!
I am simply a bailiff here. If you want to help, seek out Constable Agazu. You can find her around the town square.nnBut if you add to our woes, stranger, you shall have to answer to me.
We meet again, <<1>>! I never doubted that you would find your way here.nnOur reunion is fortuitous. Again, we find ourselves in need of your talents.

These Knights of the Flame, they insult King Fahara'jad by refusing me entry. nnI have an urgent message for Duke Nathaniel and I am a close friend of the Duchess. I cannot understand why the Knights are so stubborn.
Verandis is dead. I thought he would outlive us all.nnThis is strange. Should I be upset or sad? I think I should just feel relieved for him.
I apologize for doubting you. You are indeed a worthy duelist.
You're stronger than I expected. You have my respect.
I wouldn't have expected such skill-at-arms from an outsider, but I saw you dueling over there. nnGeneral Thoda did too and he would like to speak with you. You will find him through the door.
The <<1>> is the last champion left. nnYou know, I think I'll wish you luck.
May the Herdmother crush all harpies beheanth her cloven hooves!
We have you to thank for my neighbors' freedom. Our families bless you.
Judging by the smell, you're carrying spider ichor, and a fair bit of it, I'd say.
Why did we listen to Veraya?nnWe should have been more suspicious of an outsider who wanted to see our shrine!
One day, I'll be a master smith. Then I'll make the best swords in the land.
Hurry, <<1>>!nn<<2>> must be stopped!
Spirits of my line, watch over me.nnGuard me and give me the strength to reclaim our home.

By my bones, I have not felt so rotten since the day my kin of the horse tried to teach me to ride. I was thrown to the ground. I felt broken for weeks!nnI can only hope Jonnedor doesn't feel that same pain.
Forgive me. I am not my usual self.
Now the arena champions are dead, I assume you plan to take their place. nnIf not, there goes the business.
I heard the count's having those prisoners released.nnNo bad thing, if you ask me.
Fair weather today, except for the Nords everywhere. nnDo you need passage?
Is it done? Have you avenged my brothers?
We surely would have perished in that cave if not for your heroics, <<1>>. Thank you.

<<1>> is contested by all three alliances of Tamriel. It's a constant battlefield. Dangerous, yes, but this may be an advantage.nnReinforcements are constantly being sent to Balfiera. You should have no problem joining up and shipping out with them.

The dead cannot hold a soul fast. In his greed, Karnosis left these bodies alive, but soulless.nnUse the Soul Gem from the <<z:1>> to transfer the souls from each <<z:2>> to a nearby body. Once the soul is anchored,  destroy the body to send it on.
It's all so much clearer than before. The visions come bolder than ever! But have I spoken well, I wonder? Have you understood what I've seen?
I'll keep an eye on my brothers. Use the apple to encourage the foals to return home.
Ah, it's you! Did you enjoy that apple? There's more where that came from, friend.nnOnly one sample per customer, I'm afraid. You'll need to pay for anything else you buy.

Before you can reach Shiri, you'll have to unseal the vault. Destroy <<1>> and <<2>>. Then collect blood from their undead husks.nnYou'll also find two of the three Ansei Wards on the fallen liches. Perhaps you can save them from their fate.

The quickest and safest way to get to Evermore would be by boat. One of the harbormasters outside of Sentinel can help you with that.nnYou will most likely find <<1>> on the docks in the city. I've heard it's the best place to find information.
I told you everything I know. Talk to Martine.
Was that a fight I heard? Looks like you didn't need any help.nnLeveque's likely still up there. Go get him.
That's a mixed bag if I've ever seen one.nnWe have little time to train them, but train them we must.
I'd get that information to <<1>> right away. It's probably important.
<<1>> is the one to talk to.
As I said, talk to the Captain about any suspicions you may have.
I made it this far. We hillmen are as stubborn as we are strong.nnDid you find what I need for the cure?
Use the portal and speak to <<1>>. You'll find him in Sentinel.
Come on! What are you waiting for? Let's go!
Alik'r is in your debt. Thank you!
Your brave actions have saved Alik'r. Thank you!
<The dog barks and wags his tail in recognition.>
What news? The safety of the royal family depends on this.
Friends can be expensive.

<<1>>, you have done so much that I could not. I do not question your reasons. Greed or glory, or anything between the two, is reason enough for me.nnShall we take the last steps up the tower together?
I mourn the creatures you were forced to kill. They usually aren't so aggressive.
I'm taking my family to Daggerfall. We'll be safer there.
I will always remember Daggerfall's champion.
Assassins in my port? Thank Tall Papa you were here.
Let's turn that stupid pig into pork chops and be done with it!
A swineherd's life isn't easy, you know. But my pigs love me.

Hold, stranger. If you're going toward Shornhelm, you're doing it at your own risk. nnAs much as I'd love to tell you the Shornhelm Guard will keep you safe, that's just simply not the case. We're spread thin and trying to regroup.
I know why you're here, but where I got that amulet is a discussion for another time. nnJust be careful. The werewolves won't appreciate having their secrets revealed.
I never thought it would come to this. A civil war has begun in Rivenspire. Finn and I are all that's left of Shornhelm's militia.nnWas Oldgate attacked? Do their defenses still hold?
You're looking for someone? I'm keeping records of who survived and who was lost.nnGive me the name, and I'll let you know if he or she survived the attack.
I finally made it.nnWhat did <<1>> say? Is she ready to accompany me to <<2>>?
That's everything. I'll have my guards get ready.
Be careful out there. Red Rook bandits might be anywhere.
Talk to the captain. She's in charge.
I'm glad you got out of there without too much trouble. Did you get rid of their posters? I don't want more desperate farmers turning to banditry this close to Daggerfall.
We were able to get all the villagers through the portal. They're safe in our camp for now.
So it was Angof. I thought I smelled the stench of true evil.
Friend, the poor of Daggerfall owe you our lives. We don't have anything, but if we did, we'd give it all to you.
I learned a hard lesson. I won't turn away anyone who's in trouble again. Not on my watch. Not even a beggar.
Well it's time for you to go back to Ashton and ask her to let you take the journeyman test. Be careful  the last apprentice who did that mysteriously vanished.

I cannot emphasize enough how dangerous this situation has become. nnIf the king does not recover quickly, this may be the end of the Daggerfall Covenant.nnI beseech you to do everything in your power to help him.
The air feels so nice out here.
I can start a new life. A better life.
Let's go. The longer we stick around, the more time I have to change my mind.
Now, pay attention to Recruit Gorak. He's a great scholar of our history, and has all the makings of a fine soldier.
Watching you fight was amazing.nnI hope I can remember what I've seen today.

Do not linger here, stranger. The fight is still in your hands. You still have much to live for. My days will end here, where they should, next to my wife.nnGo now. Do what I could not. Protect those who deserve to live.
By the Eight! He killed them. Get in there and destroy the Duke. I'll make sure he doesn't get past you. Go!
What are you waiting for? The Lion Guard doesn't tolerate sluggards.
You found Bethany! nnBut what about the rest of the women? Do you know what the Bloodthorns did with them?
Alik'r is in your debt. Thank you!
Your brave actions have saved Alik'r. Thank you!
Get to the city quickly. Inform the Lion Guard how to beat Faolchu and they may yet have a chance to take Camlorn back.

Off with you now. Bumnog will help you. Interesting fellow. Always fights fair. Refuses to use weapons against the harpies. Just his fists.nnCan't imagine that that works out for him, but he's the only Dagger still here, so what do I know?
Listen, you've helped the Daggers. A lot. And we appreciate it. But before we go back to camp, I need to make sure you understand something.
Did I hear you harassing my workers? Ohama says she sent you to look for a thief among them.nnI'm not sure I believe her story, but I'm willing to hear her out.
Lord Diel seems kind of angry. But I'm sure Gelvin can straighten everything out.
Remember to burn the tent. You need a distraction to place the eggs in Diel's bed.
A harpy attacked his lordship? No, I didn't see a thing.
We're not warriors. I'm a potter, for Stendarr's sake! We were lucky you came along.
You are ready to face <<1>>.nnWait to use the charm until she tries to drain your vitality. The charm will turn her magic against her, revitalizing you.
My time is short. I won't live to see many more days.nnThat's probably a blessing, but if you can do this, perhaps Sonia and I will be reunited one day.
I've lost everythingPoppa, the lighthouse, everything. nnHow can I go on?
I heard screams at the temple, then . They came so fast, up from the <<1>>!nnI don't know what to do! Some fled, but there are still people in there. They need help!
I told my mother to meet me in Lainlyn. Have you seen her?
Do not return here expecting to find me, <<1)>>.nnI am needed elsewhere.

Excellent! You have the scorpion claws! Go speak with the master's son, <<1>>. nnHe's near the entrance to the stables with a few of the remaining guards. He should have another task for you from the stablemaster.
Thanks to you, the Daedric attacks have subsided.nnWe are in your debt, <<1>>.
The lamentations of Westtry's dead have silenced. Thank you, traveler.
Do you have the hawthorn berries? Take them to Muriel. She's in her shop on the town square.
Captain Rosalind! I've been making poultices for the wounded, but I'm out of hawthorn berries.
Captain, I went by your house to check on Leon. nnHe was praying, but something wasn't right.
We were hard pressed for a while, but their attack seems to have slackened.nnHow did you fare?
<This corpse was stabbed and slashed beyond recognition.>
Now that the portal has closed, the Daedra have been confined to Oblivion again. I salute you, <<1>>!nnUse this gateway to return to the at-Aswala family. Tell them of your victory.

I see that <<1>> is no longer disturbing the temple grounds. Thank you for your help.nnTell me, what more have you found? Is the Worm Cult truly a part of this, or was I seeing phantoms where none need be?
We're lucky you came along. nnBut I'm sure our luck won't last. Have you seen the crocodiles around here? We're going to wind up as a meal for one of those monsters.
Well, I guess I've learned a few things they don't even teach in the Lion Guard.
Gada, Gada, Tobr'a Netu nnNo. That can't be right.
That took longer than I hoped. It's hard to be patient when I know the fate of my kingdom is at stake. nnTell me you have good tidings  or did they escape with the Ansei Wards?
Guy and Erwan should be along the south road, the one that splits toward Aldcroft and Camlorn.
Guy and Erwan should be along the south road, the one that splits toward Aldcroft and Camlorn.

I wish I could've fought by your side, <<1>>. My blade thirts for vengeance! For the moment, your victory has given me solace. nnTake the scorpion claws and Daedra hearts to my father in the tower north of <<2>>. May our ancestors watch over you!
Grahla actually agreed? You can look for the door into the past? Well, that's just great. I knew she'd appreciate what I'd done.
Well, at least I can say that Sarvith's spells are consistent. They never fail to fail.

The caves are down by the docks, set into the cliffside there. You may have to get your feet wet a bit to get there.nnDo me a favor though - when you get there, don't mention my name. Alright? I promise I won't work for them anymore.
This armor is your key to the past. It belonged to my beloved and was buried in this place of honor. nnIt was my beloved's hand that cut Faolchu down.
This isn't an easy choice, I know. I don't envy you. nnBut whatever you decide, we're with you.
The orders must be on one of the Alessian soldiers. Find them and meet me back at the camp.
Well, <<1>> what do you need?
The choice has been made and the end approaches.nnI'll join Leon in our home. Come to us after you complete the task.

The Withered Hand attacked us in the night. I fear their warriors have slain all my brothers and sisters.nnWe have failed in our sacred duty to protect this foul ground from the dark arts. If only you had arrived with your warning sooner!
Curse this darkness! I can't see a thing!nnAre you another one of <<1>>'s illusions? Don't think I'm a foolI know your tricks!  Where is <<2>>?
<<1>> dislikes the undead.
You are beyond brave to challenge the Bloodthorn cult like this.nnSo how did you fare? Is the <<1>> secure?
As soon as you capture a <<1>>, take it into the circle at the center of the standing stones.nnThen we'll be ready to perform the ritual.

The Iliac Rider is anchored at the northern end of Aldcroft's docks. Head east through town to get there.nnRemember that each coffin aboard that ship has remains that could be raised as an undead abomination. That cannot come to pass!
Do not speak to me while your promise is unfulfilled.
Greetings, <<1>>. nnIf there is any way I can be of service, please let me know.

Greetings, <<1>>nnAs you know, the Mages Guild asks that all members do their part to destroy the Cold Harbor anchors, dispatch the creatures that have come through, and return any artifacts to learn more about that realm.

Greetings, <<1>>nnAs you know, the Mages Guild asks that all members do their part to destroy the Cold Harbor anchors, dispatch the creatures that have come through, and return any artifacts to learn more about that realm.
Sir Granden's tomb is in the eastern mounds. nnBeware. He was strong in life and will be strong in death.
We made it in, thanks to you. nnWith the gate locked, we should be able to hold this position.
Hello <<1>>! I'm at your service. Is there any information I can provide?
It's good to see you. Is there something I can help you with?
Now that <<1>>, <<2>>, and <<3>> have returned to the earth, I feel at peace again.
You must act with the honors, of course. Replace the relics on their respective altars.
Thank you! You made my wife very happy.nnI would have handled this myself, but my wife refused to hear of it. She worries so about me.
Once you acquire my lockbox, please hold onto it until we're safely away from those dastardly bandits.nnAnd do be careful. I'd hate to think that someone got hurt trying to help me.
I hear you were instrumental in the defeat of that villain, Angof. Well done!
Is the Duke safe?
That didn't seem right.
We can't fail here. Our families, our homes  we're going to lose everything to that beast.
I always believed in Alinon's research. That's the reason I agreed to help him.nnWe hold the key to ending this curse. Let's just hope we're not already too late.
I'd be in terrible trouble if you hadn't come by when you did.nnAnd I'm ever so grateful. Really.
Thank you for directing the women here. They will be well cared for.
<<1>>. Hhhmph. Good to see progress. nnReady for test? Journeyman forestry awaits.
You destroyed the tunnel under my home?nnGood. I hope it fell on the heads of hundreds of those murderous Imperials.
Angof's evil flows deeper than the wellspring of this land. This must end quickly.
Rescue some of the villagers, and Tamien will trust you enough to let you in.
You made it! I was worried about you.
I got here as soon as I safely could. I'll make sure my brother's wounds are tended.
Please assist my warriors in slaying the undead.nnThen speak to our tribe's shaman, Zal at-Zazir. Learn of his success in curing the poison.
I tried to hold on as long as I could. The pain was overwhelming, stranger.nnT-Tell me  were you successful in killing the undead?
The siege camp is ours again, but at what cost? And do we have the forces remaining to continue this course of action?nnI'm not so sure.
You! I am so glad you made it in time! We are just about to begin the ceremony.nnCasnar told me everything, and knowing what you have done, you are the guest of honor!
Do you often just walk into people's houses and snoop around upstairs? nnIf my cousin were here, he might not be so friendly. Me  I don't care. I don't really care about anything at this point.
The more I think about it, the more this concerns me. If you find my brother, tell him to come speak with me. nnIf he doesn't come soon, I'm going to close up shop and help you search.

Slow down now. You've made your point. Like I said, I'm a businessman. Truth is, I didn't much like the deal I had with Jagnas anyways. nnYou'll owe me a favor, but I'll give him a refund, and your boy can get married whenever he likes.
Nobody boards this ship without the captain's password.nnSpeak the password or walk away.
I prayed to the Eight for a miracle. Instead they sent you. nnOh, don't look at me like that. I'm joking. Mostly. Now go get that key.
Who are you? How  how did you get past my soldiers?nnI surrender! Please, don't hurt me.

We must destroy this tunnel to <<1>>. The smuggler who built it is long dead, and the empire he was avoiding no longer has teeth.nnWith the tunnel destroyed, the Imperials and their Withered Hand allies will be denied easy access to Satakalaam.
I can feel the oppressive weight of Angof's corruption lifting. I sense the gratitude of the guardians, but I also sense  fear.nnAngof's vermin are afraid.
Thank you for dealing with the trouble on our docks.nnThe risen dead are an uncomfortable subject.
I heard you did a good thing at Kulati Mines, dealing with those spiders.nnI was glad to hear it. I just don't know where we're going to get our ore shipments, now that the mines have shut down.
I've come on behalf of <<1>> to deliver an invitation to the palace.nnThe king wishes to personally express his gratitude for your efforts here today.
You saved many lives today, <<1>>.nnBahir made mention of the "Withered Hand." I fear what this new group may mean for Sentinel.
It's good to see you again, <<1>>. I take it you spoke with <<2>>? I was just filling in Zafira on the details.
Please channel more energy into the storm shard. It's the way to save me!
Watch yourself out there. The Ra-Netu are clumsy, but if a few of them get a hold of you  well, I saw what happens, and it is not pleasant.

You did good here. I'm sorry about the bandit's father, but the two of you saved a lot of lives today.nnIf you speak to the bandit, let him know we'll look the other way if he decides to slip out of here. Meanwhile, we've got a town to clean up.
Unclawed traitor! Ildani never should have trusted you! nnYou betrayed this one. The Baandari will know. They will not forget.
Did you bring the contraband?
Did you track down <<1>> after you killed <<2>>?
Were you able to find <<1>>?nnI lost him somewhere in the desert outside of <<2>>.
The curedid it work?
The tension's so thick, the suspense is killing me! I hope Gelvin gets out here soon.
It's not far, let's keep going!
Satakalaam is saved.nnMay Tall Papa be praised!
You did it! The Imperials will regret ever setting foot in Bangkorai.
Thanks for helping the people of Deleyn's Mill. Maybe we'll go back and rebuild after things finally calm down.
You walk toward me with such purpose ... is there something on your mind, my son?
Be wary of those vines.nnWherever they appear, the Bloodthorn cult isn't far behind.
I'll admit it. I didn't think you could do it, but the guard captain is gone, and things are looking better by the day.

Ha! Strastnoc's head! I thought we were in for a long standoff with that skeever son-of-a-cow. Then you walked up and dropped his head in my lap! nnI've been fighting with these milk-drinkers too long. Well met, my friend. Well met.

Aha! You must be the hero whose bold deeds Captain Hjurrun was just recounting. Retaking the lighthouse may seem trivial, but in times like these, it's huge.nnSay, you look like someone I've been hearing quite a bit about. Might I ask your name?
Who's that? You again? I told you. I'm not risking my family until we have a way to defend ourselves. Bring me those weapons and I'll open the door.
I do hope you find Lady Laurent quickly and let her know that supper is ready. nnI found those little gherkins she likes so much.
This crown is quite a marvel. nnBut why is Stibbons acting so strangely? No doubt it's all this open air. He's not cut out for adventuring. I'm sure that's it.
By Kynareth's breath! I've already noticed fewer undead emerging from the tombs.nnHave you finished consecrating the tombs?
The aura of an undead hand touches you, <<1>>.nnPlease tell me the abomination you found was not Ishan!
Hope you found what you were looking for. I've got to get back to work.
<<1>> has been freed from his madness.nnI wonder if he'll repent his actions?
<<1>> made a noble sacrifice.
That'll teach those mangy beasts.nnNow press forward! We must maintain our momentum.
These werewolves were much tougher than the ones near Aldcroft. Nice work getting us in. nnIf you're trying to impress me, you're doing a good job. Keep it up and maybe we'll talk later.
How long will my descendants be cursed by my actions?
We packed some survivors out. Is the job done?
The portal is open for you to use.nnPlease be quick. My master is not known for his patience.
I helped you get this far, so return the favor and free me from this prison.
Some of the miners came through here, saying you helped them. Are you all right?
Tu'whacca's Throne is far to the northeast. nnMay the Eight guard your steps, <<1>>. I pray we aren't too late.
You've helped ease our suffering, if only for a short while.
There you are! I was beginning to worry. It seems that more and more of the dead are rising every minute.nnDid you learn anything in the crypt?
Meet me in the town of Satakalam to the northeast. My vision of the tragedy there is blurry.nnI fear what the details may show.
You must choose Queen Therese. The alternative is ... unthinkable.
I hope Adrien will find some measure of rest.nnHe was willing to sacrifice everything for Bangkorai, but eventually, he would have become just as much of a threat to it.
It's good to see you again, my friend. The Shornhelm Guard has been helpful, but my mother and little brother have yet to arrive.nnBy any chance, did you happen to find them while you were out there?
I knew you'd figure out that old riddle. It's one of the favorites of <<1>>.
Safe journeys to you. Wherever your path leads, remember what you've learned at Leki's Blade.
If I can do anything for you, just let me know. I'll do what I can for those who protect our people.
You return! Have Angof's minions fallen before your wrath?
It's awful out there. I hate war. I just hate it!nnAnd I want my mother. Why isn't she back yet? I want to go home!
Elian's a tough customer, isn't she?nnShe'd make a great dockworker.
Have you laid my family to rest?
You again? I thought you'd be wearing an iron collar at the bottom of the river by now. nnWhat in the blazes do you want?
Greetings.nnIt's nice to see another strong guild member around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that.

I know her Majesty would appreciate if you gave these matters the highest priority. After you've completed your investigation, come speak to the queen at the Chapel of Saint Pelin. nnIf there are problems, she should know as soon as possible.
Take care you know your place in all this, <<1>>.nnPolitics can be as treacherous as a double-edged blade.
Emeric may be High King, but I control my destiny now.nnTell him I appreciate his offer, but I must remain here.
I'm sorry I snapped at you.nn<<1>> thinks the Imperials are doing something with these gargoyles. She's always had a soft spot for creatures like these.
You're not another messenger, are you?nnI'm embroiled in discussions and have no time to attend to the whims of other foreign dignitaries.
Now that things are settling down here, perhaps you can assist me with a more mundane task.
Greetings, <<1>>.nnIt's nice to see another strong guild member around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that.
Nice to see you, comrade. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that.
