Well that takes care of that, now doesn't it?nnI'm actually quite relieved. It would have been so embarrassing to have been responsible for the fall of Alik'r. After I opened the portal, I considered just leaving and denying that I was ever here.
You have answers? Answers are more to me than water! Answers! Answers!
Poor, craven Stibbons. The truth is, I almost feel for him. Almost.
Stendarr's mercy, I never thought it would come to this! The Orc said it would be a simple job. Easy gold! That's all I was trying to do.nnIf you let me live, I swear I'll never do it again!
What else does the fleshling want?nnThese branches have nothing more to offer.
Have you crafted the ring?
The riches of Dresan Keep were almost within my grasp!
The wards on the vault entrance have been removed. You are free to go.
What a magnificent find! I doubt Richard appreciated its value, though. He sought treasure, not knowledge.nnI'll see that the Dresan Index winds up in the proper hands.
Your deeds precede you, <<1>>.nnThe corruption of necromancy was anchored in our harbor, but you have cleansed us of that evil.
Shurkul has the recipe. Talk to me once you have learned it.
Still hanging around, eh?nnDon't suppose your reconsidering that drink? Ah, nevermind. We both have things we need to do.
Do you have the ring.
Antieve has the recipe. Once you learned it come back and talk with me.
Cut me down before the spiders return!
Well, what are you waiting for? Cut him down!
Once, the Viridian Sentinel stood for something more than a wetnurse to spoiled children. Now, he expects us to train and rear this daughter of the city as our own?nnNo. The Sentinel asks too much.
I suspect this priest has fallen from Arkay's favor. That explains why he's making such a big deal out of nothing. nnSo what if the holy water burns! That doesn't prove anything!
When you find Angof, hit him once for me.
You already have the achievement! Quit bugging me.

I've known Stenwick since I was a child. Just because we didn't agree on many things, doesn't mean his burial tradition should be ignored.nnWe'll return Elara's body to Evermore. I don't know how royalty prefer to be buried.
You already have the buff hurry up and investigate the stuff at the top of the ramp before it wears off!
I need to finish drawing what energy I can, and then get Elara back to my hut. I've done all I can for her here.
You managed each fight well. There should be no lasting effects.
I sent my own to make sure she didn't leave. As you can see, the threat is no more.nnThe Sentinel-friend will inform <<1>>, is that correct?
I'm sorry, I wish I could join you in the fight, but someone's got to keep watch on the road in case the Reachmen get reinforcements before we do.
I can't go back in there, I can't fight them they're relentless!nnGods, it's happening again, the long hand of the witchmen closes in all around us.

If you think that I will let them parade me down the streets of Evermore, you're mistaken.nnAll I need is a sharp stone and for him to look away, then it will end. You've gained nothing! And I  I have nothing left.

You are like a bottle of iced Collequiva in this dreary desert. Hopefully this will restore Lady Laurent's confidence in me.nnI still can't understandhow could she doubt me after so many years' service?
Ah, <<1>>! I'm glad you returned safely. It seems the princess will recover, thanks to your timely intervention.nnI don't think I'll be as fortunate. It's about that time for this old dog, I suppose.
We must gather the motes. Quickly, before they're gone, and the Viridian Sentinel's power with them!
It's nothing like I imagined it would feel  so cold.nnBut this will be worth it. The Imperials will be destroyed.
It's been a fine adventure, I must admit.nnMay our paths cross againparticularly if we're on our way to a rowdy tavern.
I recognize this place. We're in the temple at <<1>>.nnLittle has changed since I was alive.
Her Majesty hasn't changed a bit.nnWell, perhaps she's a bit thinner, but that's to be expected.
I wonder what's happened to cause such unrest here.nnIn the past, Pelin Temple was a place of serenity.
I regret the day I ever involved myself with these Red Rook bastards. nnBy the Eight, this ends here!
You  cast my spell? The masking ritual? But why?
Well, champion? Ready to receive your reward?
Gelves and his Red Rooks are worse than a plague. They're worse than Daedra. nnIn fact, they're worse than a plague of Daedra!
You found my <<1>>! I was worried that I'd lost her forever.
What answers the call is the Hunger. Has it been sated?

The contract between the Saltwalkers and the Withered Hand was broken before it even began. And those mercs now consider us blood enemies.nnI'm tempted to offer you a percentage of the coin we take from them. Tempted.
Did you speak to the witch?nnYou look like you're all in one piece, but I think I'll stay back, just in case.
We're going to get rid of the Red Rooks, aren't we?
You were right. Nothing good ever comes from giving up. We have to fight for what's ours.
The Company has broken off talks with the Hand and we will soon be rich with Satlwalker spoils. You've done yeoman's work, <<1>>. Well done!
We'll get rid of these Red Rooks for good.
I could hear <<1>> singing your praises from here. He took his wife's death pretty hard. She was a good woman, and a great fighter.
Where did I last see it? I can't remember now.
If it's not one thing, it's another. Where did those children hide my knapsack this time?
Are you ready to begin? nnRemember that I can't defend myself while I'm performing the ritual. You have to protect me.
You're back? You survived!nnWhen I heard the death cries of those smugglers, I couldn't listen I had to get out of there.
You've returned!nnI could feel a darkness lifting from this area as its halls were filled with incense.
Well done, <<1>>. Together we prevented an alliance that could have threatened all of Alik'r.
It is true! It is all true! You won the race!nnOur fates are unavoidable! Do you know what this means? Do you realize the full extent of this?
I wish I'd been there when you killed Angof. I had to get the others back to safety. I think they'll all recover. nnBut I must say  well, congratulations. You really are something.
How can I help you defeat Brinarch?
After what we learned today, I hope Sorick can push the Imperials back for good.
A splendid showing! The knighthood is reunited, and those damned Mer know what dangers they face at Farwatch Tower!
Go, go, tallfolk! Kill warchiefs!nnGather dead Dres and mage gear from Birdsnap goblins. <<1>> will sneak out in confusion with disguise!
We meet again. Have you looked fate in the eye? Did she blink?
How could this be? All he needed was a splint for his leg after his horse fell on him, and now he's dead! Why would someone kill him?
I knew this would happen.nnNow her butler has paid the price.
I pray you will find the sacred tablets, <<1>>. May Akatosh protect you.
You never fail to come through, especially when it counts.nnYou must get those bones to <<1>>. I'm certain he can unravel whatever foul curse <<2>> created.
So it's off to Wayrest you go. I wish you luck, <<1>>.
I do believe I've unraveled this curse, <<1>>.
I won't be getting out of here as easily as you will. I've already lost the hunt.nnPlease don't tell <<1>> you've found me here. If she knew, she might do something  rash.
That's not right. Something strange is going on in this town! You've seen it, haven't you?nnThey just took Draven away for their "initiation." It's like some kind of cult!
Watch out for that spirit. Who knows what harm his riddles will cause you!nnDon't say I didn't warn you.
The poor fool. He has already joined us in blood, if not in spirit. I guess there's nothing left to do, if his wish is to leave the ritual unfinished.nnHe must be put down.
You're back. Any luck?

My father's house is just northeast of us. You should find a bar of silver within the dresser inside.nnThe silver and the shards of the original medallion should allow our blacksmith to reforge the medallion.
Go on. Ask whatever you want. It doesn't matter anymore.
You have shown great skill in your hunt. Lord Hircine will be pleased.xx
Well met, mortal creature. I quite enjoyed your show of skill.nnHave you any more tricks to show, or have you come to request a boon? Better harvests? A plague upon your enemies?
Well, that last lizard didn't race so well.nnSpeak to <<1>> again. She might know how to help your lizard.
The Imperials leave us alone, for now. Keep your voice low.
I can't wait to hear the story on this one. It's not every day <<1>> finds herself injured instead of injuring someone.nnI have a feeling Muquaddim may have some explaining to do.
I told <<1>> you'd look him up once you'd helped some folks around Crosswych. nnHe's in the center of town.
Give me a moment, and I will find arms and armor that I can carry!
<The dog barks happily.>
Back so soon? nnI still have many terrific lizards to choose from. Were you looking for something specific?
That was  intense, but <<1>> has been consecrated. She will never threaten us again!nnGive <<2>> the good news. He's inside <<3>> in the manse of <<4>>.
<<1>> is waiting for you at the shrine to the southeast. When you've dealt with the necromancer's bones, report to <<2>> in <<3>>.
If <<1>> and his Withered Hand threaten <<2>> again, we will be ready. We will crush them into the sands.nnI am glad to count you as an ally, <<3>>.
The trolls are bolder than ever these days, and I  well, I'm not as spry as I used to be.
Lucas wasn't bad for an Imperial, but I think it will be safer here without him around.

Only by slaying the risen minions can we ease their suffering. You'll find them near the necrotic altars spread throughout the necropolis.nnWhen you've defeated enough of the risen minions, meet me in the tombs below.
If I was healthy, I would help you against <<1>>. She must be stopped.
His time as the Sentinel is drawing to a close.nnWe are here to fulfill our duty and return his body to the woods.
We lost a great many friends today, but it would have been so much worse if you hadn't been here. Thank Stendarr you arrived when you did!
I pray that Stendarr continues to protect us.nnThe crypt's entrance faces the shores of the lake. Stop the hagraven before she completes her ritual!
It's passed. I'm so ashamed. The feeling comes and goes, but I need to talk to someone, to take my mind off things. Please.
It's rude to interupt someone while they're eating.

In addition to the public praise, I must express my own appreciation, wayfarer.nnYou not only saved the kingdom, you also saved its king. My reign would have been buried in the sands had you not intervened. Thank you.
Sorry, I don't sell our supplies. I'm sure one of the merchants on the other side of town will have what you need.
You're back! I told <<1>> not to worry about you. Unlike some people I could name, you can handle yourself in a pinch.
I think <<1>> saved my life.nnI would have died, all alone.
Glenumbra is pretty, like Valenwood without the jungles  or torchbugs. And all the trees are wrong. Actually, it's nothing like Valenwood. nnPretty, though.
Oh no! The fact that he is not with you does not bode well. Did you find anything? Was he dead? What about the  supplies?
Zenithar guide you.nnThe Orcs of the <<1>> are blood-drinking, Daedra-worshiping monsters. They won't give up their weapons easily.
Guard me while I repair the rain catchers.
You did it! Everyone's here!
So, did you meet up with <<1>> in the woods?nnTell me, which one of you rescued the other from the trolls?
It returns! I told you to go!
I've seen peasants making their way out of the oasis. Well done! nnSpeak with <<1>> near Bergama's entrance. I'm sure she'd want to know they're safe.
I cannot believe it! Everyone survived! I only regret that it was not me who helped them.nnThey hired me for protection, not to run at the first sign of danger.
Our slain are being used against us.n nGet to the lower levels of the garrison and put a stop to that necromancer.
Good luck, deputy. We'll be watching and once we've identified all the buyers, we'll close in.nnThen you'll get your reward.
I knew my faith in you was justified.
Are you ready to help me get to safety now?
Is the necromancer dead? We will not be able to defeat the Imperials if they continue to raise the dead.
Any luck finding the sword yet?nnSo few people will work as hard as I do at these things.
I warned you, but still you took the sword! And now you bring it to my tomb? Are you deranged?nnThe sword-cursed will return soon. Take the sword away! Quickly!
Please hurry to the cave of Absolutely Certain Death and look for Willie. I'm certain nothing bad could possibly happen to you.nnYou'll find it southeast of here.
<Though the braziers have been doused, <<1>> still seems to be struggling in his sleep.>
One of those Primeval Seekers  she came out of nowhere! nnPlease! Lorelia is in danger! You've got to go help her!
Be quick and be quiet. It's better if she never realizes we were even here.
Istahn wants to free his fellows. That's enough for me to trust him.
Been a lot more guards around than usual. I hope our business hasn't gone awry.
Ever get the feeling you're being watched?nnMy father said you can't fight the law. It might be time to start taking his advice!
Have you heard from <<1>> lately? Far more guards are down here than on a normal day.nnIf this information has gone out, it could be  uncomfortable  for both of us.
Whatever their goals, the Imperials cannot be allowed to defile our ancestors.
What did you find, my friend?nnIf the Imperials aren't stopped soon, all of <<1>> could be at risk.
You came from where my comrades lie dead on the stones below. You destroyed the Imperials outside the tower.nnI know you must punish me. I am guilty of treachery  but I would do it again.

You made it here at last, <<1>>. <<2>> foresaw your arrival. I'm glad I was here to meet you.nn<<2>> assures me you are the key to defeating the Withered Hand, but to do so completely, you must defeat them in Satakalaam.

Keep bothering me, and I might forget our bargain. I might report you to the authorities!nnThe air's so dry. Only wine can slake my thirst. A pity those officers by the southern steps don't share their reserves with researchers like me.
Excellent. Quick work. Now to the Imperial camp, post haste!nnI'll hobble after as best I can and support your attacks with harsh language and rude hand gestures.
That  that wasn't such a good idea. It wasn't necessarily a bad idea, but it was most definitely not a good idea.
The King's Guards are the finest soldiers in all of Evermore.nnUnfortunately, there aren't many of them.
If the problems with the Reachmen continue, I'll have to start forging weapons instead of horseshoes.
That was immensely satisfying. I've learned a great deal from this experience. nnI will not forget.

So you are the one the tides of fate carried here to stop this transgression?nnI had watched this pathetic spirit's attempt to avoid her fate with some amusement  but I knew it would eventually have to come to an end.
I will soon take my leave of you.nnIt has been an honor fighting by your side.
My friend, you've done what I could not do alone. The Water Stone  it is no more. It is one within me!nnWhat powers await for me to discover? What forces will I be able to wield?

Be on your guard. Moira's Hope is a slaughterhouse.nnI had to fight my way out. Bloodfiends everywhere  and worse. I'm almost certain the very Lion Guards I came here to find have been turned into beasts.
These men don't deserve to suffer a living death.nnI know they'd want to be destroyed.
Yes? Something I can help you with?

We'll be joining up with the Shining Scarabs as soon as we can. Then we'll show those Imperials what happens to rats who invade a lion's lair!nnBangkorai's next harvest will be watered in Imperial blood.
Blessings upon you for helping us, but I must now find my father.nnThis man fights against the Imperials. Hopefully, once he is better, he can help me.
It appears that Red Rook may have been telling the truth. Or, at least, a version of the truth. Tread carefully. I'm still not sure I completely trust the man.
Once I was bitten, enduring the slow transformation filled me with more fear than true death ever could.nnIt was indescribable.
They're safe. Thank the Divines! And thank you for believing me.nnI'll tell you everything I know about the Red Rooks and the Bloodthorns.
Did you get the messages? Take them to Captain Gilame up on the cliffs.
Have you found the others?
The chest is right here at the foot of the bed.
I saw fire rising in the tall grass. Were you successful?
Is there something I can help you with?
I'll send word to Sir Hadir that the situation is stable for now.
The Imperials violated our graves and those of our ancestors.nnRepay them with death.
The braziers remain unlit, <<1>>.nnPerhaps this task was too much for you.
Fell's Run will heal. We're a resiliant bunch. And the mayor and I will make sure that nothing like this ever happens again.

Looks like the Captain gave you something to do. She's demanding, but she's fair. And she believes that everyone needs to earn their keep.nnJust watch yourself out there. It looks like it's going to get worse before it gets any better.
Each second those fractures remain open, another hero's corpse is being defiled.nnYou must not delay!
Prove yourself worthy. Kill <<1>>.
You don't have time to talk. You should be escorting my brother!
Is she safe? Did you save Captain Janeve?
Bad things can happen. Bad things do happen. Bad things have happened.nnWhy can I hear his whispers?
I saw some people running in from the camp! That was the missing Orcs, wasn't it?nnBut what about Leonce? If he's still in charge out there, the militia remains a threat to us all.
Renard, Elise, and Laroche all accounted for. I can't thank you enough.nnI take it you faced the creature. And your mind is still your own. You're as formidable as that beast is terrifying.

You must be the one he spoke of before he died, Andres was able to fill us in what's happening here.nnHe mentioned that he sent you after Thierry Gagnon, after Thierry and his unit transformed. Were you successful?
Do not let her win. She ran up the stairs, so be cautious.nnHallin's Stand depends upon you!
How dare you? No one has defeated <<1>>. No one!
Please hurry to the cave of Absolutely Certain Death and look for Willie. I'm certain nothing bad could possibly happen to you.nnYou'll find it southeast of here.
I don't know how much longer I can stand this.nnPlease tell me you have the medallion.
You're a valuable ally in times of trouble, <<1>>. nnWithout your help, we wouldn't have been able to save as many of these people as we did.
I had no idea. I should've spent more time checking the rumors, and less time behind my desk.
You have to help us before the Reachmen completely destroy <<1>>!nnMay Stendarr save us all!
We've stopped <<1>> here, but my scouts have informed me that they've spotted a force of Imperials heading to <<2>>.
You don't know how much you've helped all of us by ridding us of her.nnIf you hadn't come along, I can't imagine what would have happened!
Despite the concerning rumors about bloodfiends to the west and trouble in Northpoint, life here in Fell's Run has returned to normal.nnMore or less.
The Fell's Brigade will defend this town! You have my word on that.
Have you found anything yet? The stolen good? The missing Orcs?nnGet back out there and figure this out! We're counting on you.

One of my soldiers will accompany you into the barracks. This is too important a mission to leave anything to chance. Besides, an extra set of eyes to watch your back could come in handy.nnTake General Hurrent's key. It will unlock the gate levers.
I'm doing all I can. All the other heroes need to assist me!
I'm doing all I can. All of the other heroes need to assist me!
I'm doing all I can. All of the other heroes need to assist me!
I'm doing all I can. All of the other heroes need to assist me!
Help my father and brother collect the components to make harpy effigies. We must stop the harpy attacks!
You've got the apple. Herd Mother bless you and Radava.nnIf you can calm them down, I'm sure the boys will be able to get their mounts home.

Collect harpy plumes and talons from the harpies in the aeries and then place the harpy effigies at the east and west entrances to the villagennMeet my father, <<1>>, back at the Horsemen village to the south of here when you're done.
You have the rune! Now you can pass easily through the ward.nnWhatever you find in there, destroy it before Molag Bal can take part in this battle.
The patriarch is accustomed to our presence and won't harm you.nnHe's a veteran of many battles.
Ah, I was not expecting you. How did you  never mind. What news have you?
Battles are not without their casualties. Be sure to pay them back all the damage they're owed.
Something I can help you with? I'm rather preoccupied, so make it quick.
Did <<1>> send you? She said to meet her here.
The shame I suffer now is eclipsed by my happiness to have my daughter back, safe and sound. Thank you again.
You freed me by defeating <<1>>. You should speak with him. When you're ready, we can leave.nnBelieve me, I've no desire to stay here much longer.
Go on, <<1>>. The kings must be convinced.nnYou saw firsthand the fate that lies in store for us if we do not act.
It is not me you must convince, <<1>>.nnIf I had an army to spare, I would not be in this predicament.
With the duchess back on the throne, we'll soon have those Nords on the run.
What have you found, <<1>>?
Have you run my errands?
Thank you for restoring the duchess.

<<1)>>, you've done so much for me, but you are not the only one I owe a debt to. I am indebted to the people of Evermore: the farmers and peasants suffering because of me.nn<<2>> cares for those farmers. If he needs help, I must give it.
Did Captain Balmont have orders for you?
Thank you. I didn't think I'd ever get anyone here to help me.nnI don't know what he may try to do, but he looked like he'd be willing to do anything to save us.

I'll take this news back to Sentinel. On the one hand, this is good. The agent from the Withered Hand has been stopped.nnStill, I wouldn't want my next opponent to be one of the Reachmen. I'll leave that task to you.
Someone who knows what they want, yes? How can Nasir be of service?
<With it's central gear restored, the clock is ticking away.>
If it wasn't for this wound, I'd be fighting my way to the injured right now.nnDamn that arrow!
<This desk has a shallow depression in it's surface, exactly the size and shape of the map tablet you've assembled.>

Please, you have to help us! My village is under attack by the Reachmen, but these soldiers are too injured to help.nnMy father sent me to find help before the Reachmen attack again. Please, stranger. If someone doesn't help us, we're doomed!
The Mayor knows everyone in town. If anyone knows a way to free the citizens of Crestshade
I hear you're responsible for getting the dreugh on our side. Well done. nnWith those beasts chopping them up, the Covenant doesn't stand a chance.
What a plan. Vivec preserve us.nnAnyway, go ahead with it, if you've got the guts. The Three have guided you so far. Maybe it'll last.
You've been in the belly of the Covenant's beast. Tell me. Is <<1>> safe?
It's good fighting with Tanval again.

It frustrates me that someone allowed a spy to slip through into our ranks. We're going to have to take extra precautions now with the men returning from the field.nnThis just proves we need to make our move. The sooner the better.
I heard how you caught that Imperial infiltrator. Good work. Things like this wouldn't happen if we only had more men.
My acolytes know what to expect. We've already made preparations.nnSpeak to them. Give them the crown. See what true balance means.
The smell of brimstone is strong in my nostrils. Even as a spirit, this place smells of ash and death. Have you done as I asked?
Need help with a blade? I could show you a few tricks that you could try out on our little Imperial friends down there.
These Imperials haven't hassled me yet. Smart. If they get any ideas, I've kept my shiny pals here nice and sharp. nnYou in the market for a new blade? Have a look.
Nice to see a friendly face in <<1>>. It's a rarity since the Imperials took over.
A fellow mage, eh? I can tell from the distracted look. You see, an arcanist's mind is always else .nnI'm sorry, was I saying something?
Welcome to our station here in <<1>>. Hope the Imperials didn't give you too much trouble. What can I do for you today?
Can't see how these Imperials managed to take <<1>>. The Redguard of this town are better than this. We're just lucky they've left the Mages Guild alone.
These Imperials make for excellent practice.nnI admit nothing, of course, but I observe to you that practice makes perfect.
First, I end up in a desert town like this. Now the Imperials have moved in. I can't imagine what will happen next, but I hope it involves getting to use my blade.
You've got steel in your spine. I see why Tanval trusts you.nnIt's a damn shame giving up an immortal army, but the walking dead always spook the men.
I don't like the look on your face. What did you find in that cave?
<<1>> is missing? I haven't seen her. nnIt wasn't the Argonians, though. They have no reason to hate her, despite her father.
You didn't have to do that for me, <<1>>.
<<1>> has stolen the <<2>>. Even now, it dies. Quickly, into the cave. You must stop her!nnI will meet you. Soon. But first I must recover my strength.
The mountain has spoken, and Senie is no more. But we survive, and no hatchlings were lost to the flames.
Normally I hate it when he yanks me around the room with those little spells. But I've never been more grateful to him. Or to you, traveler.
Your kindness towards us is  commendable. You are kinder than I've been towards the Argonian.
You've cured the injured? Then speak to Girvas. nnTell him of the goodwill of my people. He is still in the center of town, or at least what remains of it.
Ahknara is atop the bluff? nnQuickly, f'lah, use the trapdoor behind me. Slay her before she signals the attack!
While we're waiting for an army to flank us, a second army stands ready to attack to the north. Meanwhile, assassins creep through the fort.nnThese two weeds share a root beneath the surface.
What is it  what did you find?
Good. Now use them around the edges of the fort, by the walls. Kill any assassins you uncover.
With the dreugh on our side, the Covenant is out of luck. nnSings-With-Reed saw to that. She's joined with the coral now, and I won't let either one come to harm.
The heart is yours, yet the coral lives. Once I saw it was dying, I had no choice but to merge myself with the coral. nnWe are one now: one tree with the same roots.
Did you find the bones and bless them?
Look at all my beautiful kwama! Their beady little eyes, the gentle pulsing of their abdomens. nnI can't thank you enough!
Girvas blames the Argonians for taking his daughter? What would that accomplish?nnMake this right, traveler.
You ready? Then blow the horn and give that Orc skeever the sharp end.
Oh! My lovely Nord flower. Abducted by Orcs!
I hope you believe my plan is the most reasonable one. It benefits us all in ways that may not be immediately apparent.
Thank you for finding my sisters. Have you spoken with my brother Dolril?
Place the skulls on the altar. That will bring Khralek to investigate.nnThen kill him, as he killed me.
Did you find Hjolm?
Thanks for your help with all this Maulborn nonsense. Maybe things will get back to normal around here now.
Vartis was headed toward the mouth of the pass west of here.
Ah, you're back. What did you discover?
That mad Telvanni thinks the Argonians took his daughter?nnAs my father used to say, Girvas is walking on thin ice in spring.
<You've emptied this chest.>
Hm. Don't get too many seasoned warriors showing up as new recruits, but we'll take you.nnOr were you here about something else?
Please, you must retrieve the relic before it falls into Vereansu hands! It's in the temple, down in the archives. When you have it, meet me outside the temple.
Go. Let the spirits of the past guide you.
I'm sorry you had to witness that. My friend shows great concern for Narsis. Sometimes greater than my own.nnWhat can I do for you?
You're back! Do you have the antidote?
You've come here at a bad time, friend. Ronal's sons have fallen unconscious, and people are starting to say that the Herd Mother no longer favors us.
The choice is a difficult one. Please, consider carefully, as there is no time to accomplish both tasks.
You have returned. Is he ?
I ran so fast that I nearly wore the scales from my feet.
You did what was necessary.
Sadal and I are ready to make the sacrifice.
Well done, soldier. Soon we will slay these Nede guar.
The matriarch lives? That's good to hear!nnLord Garvas will want to know immediately. You should speak to him at the stead to the north.

I'm glad all of the Othrys survived. Without them, we'd all need to find new work. Not that working here is pleasant, but it is work.nnNow all we have to do is clear those Daggerfall  soldiers out of the pools.
Misguided spawn of a rotten egg! Meddling in affairs that don't concern you.
You startled me! Are you just playing tricks on me, dryskin?
What news of my sons? Has Bjorick returned?
I'm going to make one more patrol of the perimeter. I'll meet you back inside the manor house.
Thanks for helping me out of that spot of trouble. I'll follow you to the monastery and help protect the Tear.
We must warn the hold of the imminent Goblin attack. nnGo warn Hrogar. I'll find Gar and Bjorick and try to get them to safety.
You've brought my son back to me. I can't thank you enough.
So that's what happened! I remember many mages dying, and there was something about a shield spell. nnI grew weak holding him in place. Then there was a bright light. Everything fades after that.
Get moving! Balreth isn't exactly cooperating with us.
Drathyra tells me your actions saved my wife from a painful death.nnI am in your debt. And I honor my debts.
target: Drathyra tells me your actions saved my wife from a painful death.nnTi sono in debito. And I honor my debts.

source: The shalk had me trapped up here like nix-hounds hunting a lizard.nnThank Vivec the brutes were too stupid to try going around the rock. They just stood down there and snapped at my feet.
The soldiers are gone? Thank Almalexia!nnI thought no one would come before they got tired of taunting me. They kept talking about what they'd do with their knives.
Surveying the battlefield? There will be many more. nnThe Covenant has only retreated. Now we must drive them out.
Are you here to tell me about our glorious victory? I spit on your victory.

The well leads to Shornhelm's waterways. It's a tight squeeze, but it will take you all the way up to the last house in Shornhelm's town limits.nnThe only creature you'll need to watch out for are leeches. I'm sure you've dealt with worse.

Did you hear? Martin decided to enlist! Though I will worry for his safety, I really do think this is the best thing for him, and for all of us.nnI don't know if you had a hand in this, but if you did, thank you.
Spells and sigils. Bah! Nords don't think much of that sort of thing.
Garyn Indoril awaits you.
Be wary of those who walk in the otherworld. They won't take kindly to your presence.
A fine job. Most of the herd has come home.
You are not one of the women from the Hlaalu outpost. What do you want?
You walked the Coiled Path and survived! Has the Ghost Snake spoken?
So, you were able to talk some sense into Martin? I'm glad.nnYou did a good thing. Not many people would take the time to help a common criminal like Martin Dathieu.
Search the tombs to the northeast.nnI will slip into the center of Othrenis.
Sound the whistle in front of the kinhouse. Our people will do the rest.
She just stood there, shaking! Ha! After it was all done, she still held her quivering arms out to hold me. nnOh, it was profoundly delightful. Who thought death would provide such entertainment?
Yes, it was delightful to watch her grovel. She looked like she wanted to scream and cry, but she was too stunned to speak.nnOh, that oaf is here again. How tiresome, Eanen.
The guards heard fighting. I assume you found more inside than just "evidence."
Just give me that letter and let me go. No need to get involved in things that don't concern you, right?nnPlease! Let me go!
Head to the Obsidian Gorge and report to Commander Renli.nnWe'll join you there shortly. Make sure you leave some of those Maulborn bastards for me. I don't want to miss all the fun.
Speak to him, if you wish. You might as well ask questions of the sea.
The warm-blood is skillful and cunning.
Please, talk to <<1>> who is working with some of the injuried right now.
The curse has been driven back into the reliquary. The afflicted are recovering. nnI assume we have you to thank for this?
This area is under the protection of House Redoran now. nnWho are you? What's going on in there?
Your help has been a blessing in these dark times.
Aerona's safe, thanks to you.
You look a little bloodstained. Smells like Khajiiti blood. Smells like  victory!
I'm safe, thanks to you.nnYou should speak to Captain Bannus.
Did you get the Maulborn elixir? Let me see it.
Please don't kill me! I didn't know about the ritual!
Hurry it up already! If I get caught for this, I'll be sweeping streets in Wayrest for the rest of my career.
I thought you were different. Please, just go.nnWe'll find my egg-sister and the others on our own.
Can't you see we're in the middle of a very important meeting? The fate of Narsis hangs in the balance, I dare say!
You help me disrupt this meeting and save these people's lives, and I'll find out what Madras knows.nnCatch those rats and bring them back here. There's no time to waste.
So, half of Narsis must vanish and plague must threaten the city before Ralden comes to his senses?nnAnd it takes an outsider to make him understand. Perhaps my friend isn't fit to lead any more.
I'll gather the guards and follow in your path.nnNow go. Find your ally and let's finish this.
I am obliged to call you and that merchant friends of the clan.
I still can't figure out why that Urano fellow kept asking to buy our lumber. He kept saying, "If you sold it to me, how long until you could leave town?"
You did fine work against the Maulborn. Fine work. And without a contract! I'm somewhat impressed.
Excellent. The guardians are here. Time to bind this creature.
Ah, you're a good drinking mate, friend. Come back and join us again sometime.
We Ash'abah owe you much.
<<1>> made a <<2>>? Great!nnMake sure the survivors get what they need to get out of the keep.
I'll just sit here for a while and breathe the fresh air.
Boril will send me away. I can't blame him. nnI'm grateful he didn't tell the workers what I did.
Did you find any clues? Why would someone poison Deepcrag Den?
<<1>>, you hammer every day and night, but I haven't seen you smash your hand once!nnAre you ready for your journeyman test?
The Three have not forgotten us.
Go in peace, stranger, but be quick about it.
Make your way south to the reliquary. Talk to <<1>>. He'll know what to do.
Tell <<1>> of our success. nnI now return to my eternal task.
The portal is open. The next move is yours.
The portal is open. nnDo not delay, Your living warmth is a burden to me.
This pass is too important to allow it to fall into the Maulborn's hands.
If the General seems a bit strange to you, please be discreet. He hasn't been himself lately.
The manifestsdid you get them?
So, you have my items, yes? Which do you think I should have?
If the sword had a foot, it would probably be tapping it impatiently.
You're back! Any luck finding my cargo?
Glad to have you on our side. Wipe them out.

<<1>>'s runners told me the Worm Cultists wouldn't surrender. Unfortunate, but no fault of yours. <<2>> is in your debt.nnIn truth, I feared the Worm Cult lieutenants went to our cellars on purpose, to work dark magics from within our village.
Tevynni is in charge of things now. But I still manage the stock.
Grim tidings, if <<1>> is missing.
Shor's bones, it's good to see you! The Dominion, right under our noses. Damned insidious.nnI have to warn Servyna and Heita-Meen. Quick, untie me!
Do you need me to talk slower? Check  the body  of Ruvali's dead husband. Make sure it doesn't move.
You you frightened him!
Death is not the worst of fates. Some would consider the necromancers fortunate.
Well done, my ally. Always remember you have the ear of this Dres grandmaster, should you need it.
We're all indebted to you for saving the grandmaster's son.
Necromancers deserve no better.nnGo talk to <<1>>, and your eyes will be opened.
This place was built on suffering. If we continue to enslave other races, they'll never stop rising against us.nnIt took the devastation of my home and the death of my beloved Tiril to show me this.
You confronted the Dominion at Murkwater? We have a similar problem of our own.
I knew you'd succeed where most had failed.
You've accomplished great things here. Perhaps when future generations commune with the Hist, they'll see your actions.
I keep the Hist sap warm by the fire. Otherwise, it's too thick to drink.nnOh, and you must drink the entire bowl at once. If not, we'll learn what you prefer for breakfast. Ha!
Well, you're a blue reed in yellow peat. From out of town, yes? Yes.nnYou're in luck, blue reed. Gold runs dry on long journeys, but I've got just the thing to moisten your purse.
Ah, first customer. You see what I've got. Buy if you want.
You have not "pleased the Hist" today. Rather, you fulfilled the Hist's expectations. A subtle distinction, but necessary to comprehend the Hist.
<<1>>, you hammer and quench day and night. Better yet you havenn't smashed your hand in weeks. Are you ready for  your journeyman test?
You hammer every day and night, but I haven't seen you smash your hand once!nnAre you ready for your journeyman test?

You must undergo a trial. Instead of the traditional crafting of a ring, I wish to explore your soul. Hmmm. I fear that Hastien has misplaced my soul gems. nnOh well, we shall fall back on to tradition. Are you ready?
Don't worrywe'll make sure this Ithis Omalor makes it to Mournhold in one piece.nnWe're just going to make sure he knows how we feel about him. You know, so there's no confusion.
The last fool that visited us managed to offend almost everyone in the village. Please don't say you're here to finish the job.
You can thank me for "losing" her soul gems.
<Ra-shadda cannot speak. He's gagged.>

<<1>>, it is time for you to be trialed. Instead of the traditional crafting of a ring, I wish to explore your soul nnHmmm . I fear that Hastien has misplaced my soul gems. nnOh well, we shall fall back on to tradition. Are you ready?
I don't know what to say.
Yeah, thanks. I won't forget your help. Promise.
Saryvn here has told me an interesting tale. Is he telling the truth? He says you were involved.

What was I thinking? Look at this placea few shabby buildings and a wreck of a ship. It's not a town. It's an overgrown tavern. nnThe ship's hold is filled with drunks looking for a fight. Such are the fine citizens of Alten Corimont.
Good to see you progress with the current. nnAre you ready for a test? Journeyman forestry awaits just around the river's bend.
I've seen what the plague does to a body. I won't let it take me. nnBut if the wards were destroyed .
I can see you mean business! I won't press my luck.
Excellent! A person who walks instead of rolls.nnCome on, let's get out of here.
Did you recover our stolen relics?
Go see what the fool has to say. He's out on deck. And don't waste my money.
Captain Valec should be inside the keep.
Thank you for your service.
Why are you still here? You have a spy to expose!
Have you found any signs of our missing pilgrims?
The ring? You're making it?
I don't believe it. I thought the Sentinels would make mincemeat out of you.
Don't risk your neck on my account.
Thanks to you, I will be able to perform the training ritual. These hatchlings will know the Mabrigash as their protectors.
Well done. You have proven yourself to the Mabrigash.
You really do want to help. An outlander willing to give us a chance. Will wonders never cease?

So the Khajiit didn't lie. I pegged you to make off with the money. I misjudged you.nnHere's your Dark Elf. I expect the Dominion's prize will be delivered as payment for my largess. And I have yet another present for you.
Praise Vivec, Halva found you. Whatever's in my home  it isn't my wife.
Yet another murder in Stormhold .
I heard Gethis died. No surprise there.
The wasps like you now. They shouldn't attack you anymore. Not unless you hit them first.nnThey're smart creatures. Certainly smarter than Khajiit!
It's terrible about Gethis. Stormhold used to be a good place to live. We don't deserve this.
Such a loss, all the dead  lost.
You're back, but without the keystone. What happened?
Ah, it is my new friend and leader! What can S'jash do for you?
You're back! Did you manage to deal with our Dwarven problem?
Glad you found the vicecanon. I see he was right about you.
It is over, then? nnAnd  the Ashkhan?
You smell  awful.nnNo matter. Sometimes the trials of science are not as pleasant as we'd like. You've found the items I need, yes?
I can't wait to hear the story on this one. It's not every day <<1>> finds herself injured instead of injuring someone.nnI have a feeling Muquaddim may have some explaining to do.

These Imperials . They're nothing but a hindrance! If they do anything to delay my deliveries, I don't care what the Guild says, I'll set the whole lot of them on fire!nnPardon my rant. Can I help you with anything today?
Welcome to our station here in <<1>>. Hope the Imperials didn't give you too much trouble. What can I do for you today?
Can't see how these Imperials managed to take <<1>>. The Redguard of this town are better than this. We're just lucky they've left the Mages Guild alone.
I can't wait to see what Ufa has planned for these Imperials. Sounds like it will be a good time for all involved, unless you're one of them.
Vivec bless your steps, recruit. With talented crafters in the Halls, there's no challenge we can't overcome.
It's you again. I'm surprised you haven't left the area.
No, get away! nnOh, it's you. Did it work? Are they free?
Thanks for looking into this. I didn't know what else to do.
Who thought a letter could perform such miracles?
You've proven yourself.nnAnd believe me, that isn't easy to do in my eyes.
The Pact thanks you for joining the war effort! With talented crafters like yourself at our back, there's no challenge we can't overcome.nnAkatosh bless your wares, friend.
Looking for something with a little boost? nnIf you have questions, feel free to ask. My brother runs the shop, but I'll answer what I can.
Find Humauta. If there's anyone who knows what to do about the Dominion soldiers occupying my village, it's her.
Please, leave this one to her sorrow.
Do you have the ring?
The portal is open. Do your best to break this curse!
Rumblings from the mountain have us all on edge. Balreth is up there somewhere. nnI hope you've brought good news.
I thought you would talk to Mavos. I did not expect you to bring him along.
Have you sealed the scamp caves?
The artifact is ready. Do not unseal it until it's time.

For the courtesy <<1>> has shown me, I am honored to have you meet my wife. She tires easily, so please make your visit brief.nnYou know, I would be content to remain here with her forever, if it were possible.
Have you crafted the ring
<<1>> knows what remains to be done. The moment is almost upon us. I think  I think I'm ready.
You've got both of the essences? Quickly, make your way to <<1>>. She must be ready to perform the ritual by now.
<<1>> will want to see you right away. I'm sure she's ready to perform the ritual now.nnBy Azura, you must be a brave one!
We have the essences of wrath and fire from the Daedra. We have the hearts of the dead. We've completed our preparations.nnThe ritual can begin.
I hope you have good news for me.
Did you kill the Dreamers? Were you able to recover the crystal shards?
That'll show those cultist, with thier stupid chanting and crystal stealing!
Thank you for helping me escape.
So, where are they?
Well, have you taken it to those cultists and reclaimed my property?
You smell of Oblivion. Have you been killing daedra for me? Please say you were successful
Take a seat by the fire.nnPresently, Almalexia herself will speak to you.
<<1>>  has the recipe. Talk to me once you have learned it.
Did you smash a few of those dung-guzzling Worm Cultists yet? No? Oh, well.
Ah, just in time. The Sacred Lady asked us to watch for you.
It's rare for someone to have the honor of a private audience with the Sacred Lady.nnI admit, I'm envious. A clerk like myself isn't likely to get that sort of attention.
Spread the fertilizer over the roots of our Hist. As long as I'm with you, our guards will not trouble you.
Why are you waiting? Take a shovel to that pile, and let's break open the treasure!
Honor to you, soldier.
I won't forget what you've done for us.
Sotha Sil values intelligence and ingenuity. He builds. He maintains. He is the master of his creations.nnHe shall test these qualities in you.
What in the nine holds is going on? <<1>> is missing!
The news is most dire. <<1>> is missing!
<<<1>> does not react to your presence.>
Haven't you gone through the portal yet? <<1>> must be waiting for you.
Did you find anything suspicious?
Evermore's people thank you for your service to Queen Arzhela and all of Bangkorai.
Have I convinced you, then? Are you ready to join up?
I sense you've been meddling with Elven magic. What happened?
Perfect. Just perfect. Julianos must be laughing his divine posterior off.
You won't tell anyone I tried to dig through stone, will you?
The Lion Guard is in your debt, stranger. nnI am in your debt.
target: The Lion Guard is in your debt, stranger. nnTi sono in debito.

source: I really need some rest. When are we going to get out of here?
Gales of Kynareth! We have a working Daedric containment cell!nnI'll be the envy of every mage from here to High Rock. Of course, I'll tell them you helped.
Greetings once more, Talisman-Bearer. The ward is now active.
Now what? That cult killed all our guards. We'll never get out of here alive!
Be warned. Worm cultists are notorious for slaying travelers and turning them into undead slaves.
Please find my sister, landstrider.nnAnd if it's in your power, see that she returns alive.
Has that insect been squashed?
You're new? It's my duty to warn you: there's been a series of murders and kidnappings.nnI'd wrap up your business here quickly. Oh, and welcome to Stormhold.
You have potential, my friend. I can tell that you're a very talented individual! Talk to the magister if you want to join the Mages Guild.
Quickly, speak with Elder Seven-Bellies. Pash-Riha has not returned and his concern grows.
The whole temple shook! What happened?
I've never seen such a thing. That Orc survived what no mortal should.
What do you say? Do you have what it takes? Are you ready to join the fight?
Fine goods for all chain-breakers! C'mon over and take a look, comrade.
I hope you'll be able to get into the manse. If the grandmaster's son isn't rescued, we'll never get rid of the Vanguard.
Ah, it's you again. The child whose soul was stolen.nnMy Lady Almalexia is grateful for the aid you gave <<1>>.
Have you met up with the troops to the northwest?  Please do, we need their numbers to defend the town.
Talk to Varon about the next steps. All my brilliant ideas at the moment just involve avoiding the plague.
Please, you must let me take this stuff back to my family, so they don't starve.
I think they're all here!
Thanks to you, the corruption of the swamp will wash away with the spring flood. nnI can't wait to get back to scavenging trash again.

Serien plans to keep us out with magic, eh? Well, he's about to face one of the greatest mages in the Pact.nnTo take down this ward, Garyn and I will need two foci. They're probably in the storage areas in the courtyard.
Thanks for rescuing our scavengers from those crazed plants.nnWe could still use your help. Well, <<1>> asked me to ask for your help, if you've got time.
That was quite a show you gave us. The Dominion certainly won't forget it.
Are you here to help?
The fires of retribution warm the heart, don't they?
The Dominion won't forget this day.
Hissmir is northwest of here. It should be easy to spot, since it contains some of our larger structures.
Thanks for helping out with those stranglers. They're ferocious.
You've been gone for some time. How'd it go?
Make them pay. Deal them a blow they can't ignore.
Head into the Ashlanders' tunnel. Use a pickaxe to weaken the supports. We'll hold them off here.nnI won't wish you good luck. That's for children and Altmer. I'd rather trust in your skill.
You brought our leader back to us. He may be a bit rough and tumble, but I don't know what we would do without Dolril.
Be welcome and wallow, my friend. I will not forget what you did for my cousin.
I will go to the top of the xanmeer and begin the ritual. See you there after you've placed the potions.
My family's townhouse is nearby. I'll meet you there.
Alchemists pay handsomely for kwama cuttle.
Harvyn's a bit odd, but he loves the scribs.
Gah! Where did you come from?

You must learn Vox's secrets before you can hope to face her as an equal.nnSearch for the three anima archives within. Let them pull you into the realm of memory. Let them show you how this little drama came to be.
Did you do it? Yuck! What's all over your boots?
Somehow  somehow I feel better! I don't know what happened, but I feel great!
The cave's smack in the middle of <<1>>. The Dominion's locked it tighter than a High Elf's fundament. Might have to knock a few heads to get past them.
While <<1>> recovers, we should plan to recover this <<2>> from the Dominion. What do you know of its whereabouts?
I need a moment to recover. <<1>> will be eager to hear what happened in there.
Thank you for helping me. I didn't want to become snake food.nnRagara and the others are outside, if you're looking for them.
Face down in the sand isn't the way I wanted to go out. Divines bless you for saving me.
They didn't pay us enough for this job.
Do I still look poisoned? I feel different. Gods, I bet they laid eggs in my head!
It seems you've managed to round up my clumsy mercenaries. Thanks for saving them.
How could Neposh have done such a stupid thing?
Sep murmurs contentedly in my soul, friend. You must have been successful.

Looking for the heretic woman? She went into the temple. She's probably haranguing the curate.nnShe says she wants to avoid bloodshed, but that's not really in our hands, is it? It's her kin outside the walls preparing to attack, not us.
If you're here about the job, I'm afraid it's already been taken. I can't afford to pay for the same job twice.
You stopped the skin-stealers in <<1>>. I can go home!
These ward stones are the only thing stopping us. Disable them, if you can.
I've betrayed everyone. I've betrayed the entire Pact.
You've started me on the path to redemption. nnBy the Three, I will not let the Pact down. Sadal will be bound again!
Thank you for doing what my brothers and I could not.
Thanks for helping clear out that mystic pollution.nnWe're back to normal. Just the usual filth from upstream.
Wait! What's happening! I protest! I protest!
You return.
Your results?
You're far too delightful for the horrible death awaiting you. After all, we've grown so close. Such a pleasure should be mine alone to deliver.
It's amazing what you've been able to accomplish.
What tales did the dead men tell, my friend?
Find a way to kill <<1>> and I'll reward you handsomely.
Back so soon? Are the Stonefalls dead drops done?
We wish you luck. I hope you can find my father.
Did you pray to the Night Mother? As I feared, <<1>> rouses the Shadowscales against you. There's not much time.
We heard a commotion outside. What happened? Did you find my father?
Now you know the gift Shadowscales bestow upon the worthythat life itself contains no guarantee beyond suffering.
I'll petition the Night Mother. She's granted me the right to duel you before the enclave.

I do not fear the artifact, and thus it has no power over me, for now. Still, it's power is corruption, and I don't plan to test my resilience against it.nnDon't worry. I will take care of it before it does more damage.
Keep an eye out for my fool son while you're out there, will you?
I pity the prisoners, but without the keystones, we might not be able to defeat the Dominion.nnI received a message. The Dominion made their move against <<1>>.
Do you think she truly loved me? The words we exchanged, they couldn't be said without .nnWhat am I saying  none of it was true.
You found her, didn't you? I felt it. The rain and sun blended together. nnKnowing she and I will meet again comforts me. Thank you.
Did you hear? Someone murdered <<1>>.nnIf you find out who it was, stick a sword in their guts. We can't offer a bounty, but you'd have our thanks.
Time to go. Always more scouting to dothere's still a war on. I hope you find your path well, my friend.
What happened? If <<1>> is with you, where are the others?
Hurry, Mavos cannot hold Balreth much longer.
Search the mud piles. If the dreugh captured the tree-minders, that's where we'll find them.
Now you know the gift Shadowscales receive from the worthythat pain may be conquered by ignoring one sense and embracing another.
I'd rather be a warrior with broken fingers than a man with a broken mind.nnPlease, set us free.
You set my companions free. What power do you bring to this realm?nnCould you release me as well?
In defeating Vox, you have shown the world what the Dunmer are capable of. You honor the memory of Saint Veloth.
Hurry, my friend. The goblinization spell matrix I cast on him will only last so long.nnI don't want to think what would happen if his appearance changed in the middle of that camp.
The Spell Gem will get you into camp, but make sure to avoid the clan's spiders. They'll see right through the illusion and attack.
I ran so fast. I'm still out of breath. Goblins are surprisingly quick when they have something to chase!
The braziers burn atop the Xanmeers' pinnacles. Tell me, what have you learned of the Dominion's plans?
He's gone  he died for the eggs .nnDid it work? Are they safe?
Have you seen our agony? We're not like this. It's torment to endure this way.
Got too curious and opened it, eh? Didn't think I would know? nnWretched s'wit! Give it here.
I haven't lost a man, but the scamps have lost twenty. nnNow we just need to kill this Brother-thing. It's a good day, my friend.
Go, harrow the prisoners until they divulge their secrets.
Oh, my! Your backpack is yowling. I guess you found him!
We've succeeded where that withered root Doshia failed, comrade.nnHere. I will open a portal for us to return.
The last time I saw my father was at the temple.
I'm sure that even in this disaster, Tidyn would see to his duties. Check the town hall.
My brother told us what you did.nnSpeak to us no more.
Do I detect the bouquet of <<1>>?
You make lots of carnage. Khajiit is impressed.
Please speak to the grandmaster. He's sure to listen to the hero of Fort Virak.
Beautiful, wasn't it? <<1>> wanted to consume the power of the Hist, but instead he was consumed.
Sorry, but if you're here to buy iron, the metalworks is running low. A minor labor dispute, that's all.nnCome back in a few days, and I'll give you a good deal on iron ingots.
You come to buy from this one, yes? Grandmaster gives us special license to sell and trade. Many fine wares.
Welcome back from the depths, comrade. <<1>> told me you'd have something for me?
You are back. Impressive. Aelif still cannot see what the godless Dwarves might have had.nnWhat would they have that <<1>> would want?
You'll be in good hands with Merric. he's one of our best men, and an ardent soldier against the daedra.
We must stop the daedra from invading, no matter what the means.
What in Oblivion is going on around here?
Is it over? Did you
Find them. Find their ashes. I'll never find peace until we're together once more.
I felt it! When you used the keystone to free us, it was like shackles fell from my neck.
I see the trophies of some fearsome creatures hanging from your pack. It takes skill to hunt such prey.
Don't worry, outsider. I'll have the antidote ready.
Sithis be with you for purging the corruption from our swamp!nnOnce the miasma clears, we can get back to the hunt.
What happened to your spider? nnGo catch another one. And try not to be so careless.
Are you interested in helping the Guild fight the coming Daedra invasion?
That vision! A Dremora woman, talking about Merric. Why would she want my hapless companion?
The journal might hold the key in our fight against the Daedra. Grab it and we can get out of here.
If you're thinking of questioning my orders, I would advise against it. You don't know who you're dealing with here.
Thank you for saving my lieutenant.
There must be more. It can't be this simple.
Their camp is not far. Look for something reeking of their scent. Old clothes, bedding, or the like.
The keeper is sending you on an errand instead of addressing the real threat? Typical.nnToo bad the Vicecanon won't let me beat some sense into them.
You've returned. I take it you were successful?
Have you found the relics?
Should I start counting out the coins?

The destruction of that body is only temporary. It will rise soon enough, and I will be forced to serve him again.nnBut my suffering means nothing. You must free Mistress Alanwe! She is innocent in all of this!
You have the look of one also touched by death.
Just disturb that nest and the angry kwama warrior will come running. Once you deal with the pitiful creature, we can get out of here.
My sister has a knack for attracting trouble. I'm starting to get worried.
When you see your Nord friends, ask them to send troops and aid. We have plenty of relics.
I can't believe we survived that! You made the right choice, I think. Anything else would have been disaster.
They say someone infiltrated the Shadowscales. I wonder .nnPerhaps <<1>> was right about the relics after all.
I can't believe you did that  but you've done some pretty amazing things already.
What took you so long? As you can see, I've gotten  well, bogged down.nnGo talk to Saervild while I extricate myself.
You've returned. How long ago did we speak? Why have you come?nnMy hatchling  something about my hatchling .
We'll figure out how to banish the rest of these Daedra, you can count on it.
It warms my heart to see the sacred skull back in its reliquary.
Comrade! Thank you for coming so quickly.nnWe have need of you. Will you fight by our side?
Stendarr keep you safe, comrade.
As soon as I recover, I'll report to Sees-All-Colors. She needs to know what's happened here.
We'll report this to Sees-All-Colors right away. Just save Merric!
Stay moist, comrade.nnYou'll hear from us once we've decoded the journal.
The others are safe, but more importantly, you rescued our scrolls, yes?
Look what they've done to the books. They're ruined. nnAll that knowledge. Lost.
So much screaming. So much fire.
You heard the Guildmaster. nnSees-All-Colors. She murdered Jofnir.
You're still doing that thing. You know. The thing.
I don't like chicken.
Act quickly. The Dagonites are defiling the sanctuary.
You got an invitation? I can't believe someone just gave you one. I'm going to have mine framed.
Must I repeat myself? This vessel is only for those who have been invited to attend the Shad Astula Academy of Magic.
Great. Just great. This is my luck.
Thank you again, my fine, fine friend. nnDon't worry about me. I'm going to sit here and inspect every one of these bottles to make sure they're all still good. For the selling.
The keeper does not seem to be worried, but I am.
We're going to Oblivion to deal with an insane Daedric lord.nnNot the best way for a father and son to bond, is it?

Each student undergoes a test to make sure the invitation reached the right person. Students who fail are sent home.nnThose three must pass their tests. Morrowind and the Pact need them. I have foreseen it!
Were you able to find any supplies?
I suppose you take this wand and, you know, focus. Your magic. On the clucks.nnFrankly, something doesn't feel right about this.
Haven't seen you before, are you new here?
Stay sharp sailor, we're on a very delicate mission here.
What is that thing? B'vek, it wants to eat us!
Hadmar takes little friends back now. I'm sure they can be turned back into big-friend students.
What's that distinctive bottle I see peeking from your pack?
I should've expected trouble. Damn that Daedric Prince.
Good, you're here. Ready to help the guild on another important mission?
How was your research trip with the Guildmaster, comrade?
Return to Shad Astula whenever you want. nnBring us tales of your exploits. Tell us how you deal with uncanny threats and soul-crushing perils.
Since merging with the Hist, I feel so alive. I've made the right choice.
I hear the corruption. Please, bring me silence.
Are you ready at last? Carethil lurks beneath my roots, scarring them with hatred.
You've been asleep a long time. <<1>> has asked about youseveral times, in fact.nnWhat happened?
Thank the Three, someone who looks like they can handle themselves in a fight!nnMy husband's in danger. Please, help us!
Thank the Tribunal. Someone who looks like they can handle themselves in a fight.
Are you ready? Aelif is ready to get out of the city.
Have you found my son? Others return from the bog, but not <<1>>.
Merric will know what to do. This one is planning to practice her bladework while you two are working inside.
I miss the master general. Tall Papa watch over him.
Please don't damage him  much. He's very dear to me.
Do you bring moisture? What have you learned?
Toll is paid. Paid!
Check in at a guild hall from time to time. I'll do my best to contact you when I've finished.
For someone of your caliber, this mission should be simple, though not without its challenges.
Perhaps you should pay more attention to the task at hand.
Go! Our duke awaits.
The toll! The toll! The featherless one has paid the toll.
Featherless approaches! Approaches!
The Fang crawled into my mind! What have I done? I can't stop it from gnawing my thoughts.nnHelp me!
I, for one, am happy with what you did.nnBack to working with my hands instead of abusing Goblins. That's much better for an honest day's work.
You're wet, and you stink. You have my reagents?
I don't feel so good.
Have you spoken to the Sage yet? She's very wise. And forgiving! So forgiving.
Play the tune on the instruments hanging from the wall. After I've heard it once, I should be able to play it.
What are you looking at? I suggest you move along.
What did you find in the vault?
Do not worry. If the Reach attempt to take Shor's Stone from within, they will fail.
Thanks for freeing us. Can't wait to get out of this place.
Do you have my crystal shards?
It's you. Modified rapture.
Have you defeated <<1>>?
What are you doing standing around here? Go out and find those crystal shards - the realm depends on it!
If you don't find those shards we're all doomed!
Is he dead yet?
Thanks again for helping me with the Dreamers.
<cough> Please I do not have much time. Please retrive the crystals.
Thank Kyne you made it out alive!
Don't leave me like this.
Free me from these cursed vines!
What would Lodunn have done without me, eh? He'd be dead for sure.
The Reach need to be wiped out!
You have the books? Next time we're at a tavern, I'll buy you two drinks!
The other students are waiting to say goodbye. They're on the docks.

Thank you for getting me out of that mine. My husband and I are indebted to you. nnOnce things calm down, I'll get you that mead I promised. And it'll be good stuff from Hodmar's private stock, assuming the Goblins haven't stolen it.
Those bastards are to somethng. You should check them out.
No! Get away!nnOh, wait. It's you.
Thanks again for freeing me.nnNow, you should go off and have more adventures. I think I've had my fill of those.
I knew to expect you, but not one of <<1>>'s soldiers. I take it she's your prisoner? You've interrogated her, yes?
We go flying now! To the big rock! Whoosh!
Still got your nose. Greenhorn.
Have you seen <<1>>? Our scouts spotted the Dominion's main force!
Good luck, my friend.
Please hurry. If the vicecanons arrive before we get the totem, they'll just kill or enslave the Goblins again.nnThis was supposed to be a clear stream, but it is now fouled with blood.
Time grows as short as a winter's day. We must act before it's too late.
I hope you did the right thing. Who knows what these prisoners will do now that they are free.
Everything's in turmoil since those Wood Elves came here.nnWhat are they doing, anyway?
You've found the others? Was there no sign of Adana?
You saved Narir, thank you! Though none of us will live long now that Sinmur's back.
Please, don't give up, I just know Raena's alive in there, you have to save her!
<This Nord was recently killed. His belongings are in disarray, but a runestone remains clutched in his hand.>
Honor to you and your house, stranger. Have you come to deal with the ills of our poor mine?nnIt's a terrible business all around, but you could certainly help us make it less terrible.
You've found more of that curious liquid? Take it to Garm. Maybe that will persuade him to go elsewhere.
This wound isn't getting any better, not with you just standing around.nnAre you going to take care of business, or do you need me to hold your hand?
Did you come from the Serk? We sent a guard over there to check on some disturbing rumors we've been hearing.
That's a new look for you. Not certain I like it.
<The body is still warm. The cultist was killed recently.>
Tell Dajaheel what we've learned. I'll look for one of the ritual sites.
My joy, my heart  <<1>> lives! Though who knows when I will be able to provide her and her father safe shelter, at least they both live.
Welcome, welcome, to the Circus of Cheerful Slaughter! nnStep right up, my mortal friend. The show is about to begin, and you're the star!
By my father's blade! Is that a spirit?nnPerhaps  perhaps it knows where the Cartulary is. Let's get it and get out of here!
Please, traveler. Do what you can for my family.
We lost many men today, but would have lost many more if it weren't for you. Push on to the Signal Tower and warn the rest of the Rift of Sinmur's return and that Reachman army!
Great timing, traveler. I won't last long if I don't tend to this wound.nnBut  my girls are still out here. Will you look for them?
Pa told us to run. So we ran. I've never been so scared.
Father will know what to do. Grandad taught him everything he knew about surviving in the Rift.
Ah, you've returned. Do you have the second book?
Thank you for your service to the Mages Guild.
I was told I might find you here. I have an urgent message for you from <<1>>.
I was told I might find you here. I've an urgent message from <<1>>.
Thank you. You didn't have to come to my defense, but I am grateful.
<<1>> ordered me to make a list of damage. Because it's important to the Dark Elves to know how many pigs exploded under the giant's feet versus how many burned alive.nnBah.

What treachery? The Enchanter claims my liege lord's chambers! How could this .nnBy Meridia's light, I recollect it. The Enchanter decreed us slay our liege lord. We gave chase, our blades flickering like fading Varla stones, and .
Please help me! I saw you douse the fires. You have to stop the Daedra!
If you want to help us, burn us; otherwise, get out of here and stop Serien.
Please, take the <<1>> to the tree-minder and see if she can help.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
I will not speak to one who enslaves others.nnLeave. Your reward is forfeit.
Speak to your Dark Elf friends, not to me.nnRevel in the gold you earned with the flesh of others.
Have you found what we need for the healing poultices?
Well? Get moving! What kind of chateau mouser are you, sitting here while the rat runs free?
I cut down a Reach dog, and saw the smoke column reflected in his dead eyes. Nice work, ya great horker.
Is this the best place to recruit extra hands outside Stormhold? Unbelievable. It's a pit.nnAfter this, I go to Bogmother. As if the mother of bogs is a place I want to be.
I must attend to my students' bodies in the antechamber. Please, return what <<A:1>> took from them so they can find peace.
Did you get them? Did you rip apart those Daedra and take their hearts?

Don't worry about me, friend. It'll take more than losing a foot to send Hoknir to Sovngarde.nnWalking back to town was an experience, though. I think I blacked out a few times. Thank Kyne for mead, eh?
I hate running, but we don't have a choice.
My comrades have returned. I erect the spine of gratitude. You are a hero today.
I hope summoning that dragon priest works. It's the only idea I've got for getting into the barrow.
There were so many of them. We scattered. We thought we'd be safe.
How many times must I explain this? Place the runestones at the entrance to the barrow. Go!
It's the giant crystal above me!
This gives me so much to think about. I'm not sure I'll ever understand.
My brother never was the sharpest sword on the rack, but he's all I've got left.
Thanks for freeing us. Sure will be great to get out of this place.
Head inside. I'll call the others once the room is clear.
Talk to the spirit and ask it how to gain access to Skyshroud Crater.
I can't wait to get out of here.
Do I know you?
Our family is back together. I can never thank you enough.
Thank Kyne! My boat sank off the coast in a storm. It was unnatural. I saw colors I've never seen before. nnI drifted for hours on a plank. I thought I was dead.
They're alive! And they're not furry anymore!
Unbelievable! We've spent years searching for the Spinner's shrine, and these filthy creatures have been sitting right on top of it all along!
Go, go on now! He's not frozen anymore.
You've returned! Do you have the book?
Is it over? Are they gone? I don't think I hear them in my head anymore.nnYour face still drips with blood.
<<<1>> barks excitedly.>
Free others, then meet me here.
You look good in your new outfit. nnJust remember: those wolves down there will sniff through your disguise. Steer clear of them.
Have you spoken to Rana? Seen what we're up against?
What are you standing around for? Get water from one of the wells and help me put this out.
Please, fetch water from one of the wells!
Go and get a bucket of water from one of the wells.nnThey killed Maesa. I won't let them burn her smithy too.
There are buckets around the town wells. You can use them to put the fires out.

A flesh-walker joins our dreams. A welcome diversion, small one, before we rejoin the void.nnThough we soon depart, the vicecanon carries our thoughts within her. You must follow, lest we drag you to the void with us.
My friend. You've done so much for Valaste and I. I couldn't let you leave without one last gift.
Admit it  you were surprised, weren't you? The look on your face was precious!
Lead on. Aelif follows.
Who could have known we'd be standing here like this, my friend? You destroyed an artifact of the Prince of Lies. And I  I'm the new leader of the Fighters Guild.
What is that humming sound? Ah! You possess a keystone, yes?nnWe long thought them connected to the Hist. Perhaps now we're within the Hist itself, we can know for certain.
The fortress-city of Sancre Tor is one of Cyrodiil's most well-known and regaled sites. It was riskybut cleverfor Sai Sahan to have hidden the Amulet in such obvious, plain sight.
Ah, Skyrim! It's been some time since I've seen its people  and its snow.
Look, stranger. I don't deal with your type.
My job is to keep more Dominion soldiers from entering the ruin, but there are quite a few inside already.nnStay wary.
Please, will you help me? I work for the merchant, Damar. He needs your help!
We're in your debt. Most of the refugees already owe you their lives.
You had to go and be the hero at Silaseli, didn't you? Now the area's packed with free roaming beggars, cutting into my margins.
Close the master portal or they'll get a foothold in the fort!
<<1>>. <<2>> was missing you.nnThank you for bringing my family back together.
I wish I could feel safe in town, but with the Covenant in Bal Foyen, nowhere is safe.
Where did the Covenant come from?
We return to the dragon's embrace. You are a guidepost on the river's edge.
You have denied the Daggers our lives. Moisture to you.
From what I could see, things were a little unsettling in there.nnBut you got the book, correct?
Dammit, Colors. The province generals were very clear  but I've known her for so long. What will we do?
Kill her! Such lies she tells! nnSees-All-Colors killed Jofnir. She must die!
A deluded mind is a thing of beauty. It's a work of art, really.
Nice.
I always love a good deluded mind. So much like a work of art.
Thank you for sparing my life, comrade, but my scales are dry with fear.nnI believe the council is about to unspare me.
I do hope Lord Sheogorath will appreciate his gift.
They've turned you against me, haven't they? You're one of them now!nnGet out! Leave, I say! You'll never have it! It's mine!
What do you want? I've got a lot of commissions to do, so I'm busy.
Well met! What can I do for you, my newfound friend?
Damn the Covenant. My family was happy.nnWell, maybe not happy, but they were content.
If you have something to say, make it quick. I'm in the middle of negotiations.
Honestly, fear is the only thing that will get Nirar to give up that ruby.
I've even failed at this. Just leave me be. I don't want to see you or any other mortals here.
How did the training go?
As soon as my men are healed, we'll get out of here. Thank you for clearing out the ice wraiths.nnAnd thanks for letting us know the problems were a haunting, not just a coincidence.
That crazy Dark Elf has the heart of a shark.
Bring me the giant's toe as proof that the deed is done. And when you get back, I may have a treat waiting for you!
Did you do it? Did you burn the remains of the giants? And did it work? Are they going to leave us alone now?
Ha! That is a thing of beauty. Kazok's head never looked better!
With the power of the giants, nothing will be able to stop us!
If I may ask, traveler, what happened to Skorvild?
Enter the portal. <<1>> isn't going to kill himself.
Stay back. This one's dangerous.
I saw Skorvild's militia headed for the old manor house. What happened?
Ah, the power this will grant us. Soon nothing will be able to stop us.
Reaching Merric is our top priority. He's waiting on a landing in the wilds at Riverden Falls, near Aldcroft.
I have a message for you from Valaste.
Aelif is going to Ebonheart with these recruits. nnThe Daedra there don't know they're already dead. This one can't wait for them to find out.
So, how did it go?
As soon as I recover, I'll report to Sees-All-Colors. She needs to know what's happened here.
Greetings. I've a message for you from Valaste.
That demon. Who was she?nnBlade's edge, this hurts.
Has the target met an untimely end?
I've already sampled some of Roruld's first batch of mead. It's very good.
Was your search successful?
Aelif is going to Ebonheart with these recruits. nnThe Daedra there don't know they're already dead. This one can't wait for them to find out.
Nothing can replace my poor Inga, but what you've done has certainly raised my spirits.
So glad to hear you got those fires lit. I hope Davon's Watch got the warning in time.
Check in at a guildhall from time to time. I'll do my best to contact you when I've finished.
Check in at the Guildhalls from time to time. I'll do my best to contact you when I've finished.
The wolves are large and vicious, but their pelts are thick and warm. Good hunting.
You should be able to find Kyne's Breath by the rune stones scattered throughout the grove.

All of my soldiers need to be at full strength before we continue. Head back to the house my soldiers have barricaded. See if they need any more assistance, then come find me. nnWe'll figure out what to do with Ormi then.
Find Sahun at the tavern in Windhelm. Since he lost his brother, he's been drowning himself in drink.nnI'll be fine here. I just need to catch my breath.
I was a fool to turn your help down when you asked for it.nnBy Kyne, I was an even bigger fool to turn my back on my family when they needed me the most. I'll not lose sight of what matters again.
The journal might hold the key in our fight against the Daedra. Grab it and we can get out of here.
You're not from the Covenant. What are you doing here? It makes no difference. We need all the help we can get.
Comrade, <<1>> has sent me to find you.
We're here. The villagers are safe for the moment.nnBut the Covenant's still coming. We've got to get word to Davon's Watch.
Is it true? Did the Daggers get over the walls?nnEverywhere I go, they attack. Except Bleakrock. I wasn't there.
These little remains must be buried away from the problems we've had here.
They're fighting in the residential quarter, and I'm stuck here.nnI better not miss the whole battle.
You're back. Tell me, is King Jorunn well?
Misery wherever I look. How I wish Sithis would swallow the Dominion into the void.
How could I have let her do this? Oh, Gena!
The graveyard and cave are to the southwest. I hope we don't have any more skeletons before you can solve this!
I hear the Daggers have siege engines just outside the wall.nnIf a catapult shot hits my tent, will I hear it coming? Will father have anything left to bury?
Please, kill it quickly.
You're good news on a foul day, my friend.
Thank the Divines you came when you did. You made the difference here.
Congratulations! For someone who smells of southern decadence, you're fast and strong.nnThe race is yours, Champion of Windhelm!
Our business is done. Are you expecting something else?
Well done. Perhaps you should make yourself a permanent fixture around here. nnMight be fun. I could certainly use the help.
Well done. Perhaps you should make yourself a permanent fixture around here. nnMight be fun. I could certainly use the help.
It was a nightmare! A nightmare!
I don't have time to waste. What do you need?
Well? Do you wish to train or not?
What's taking so long?  Go out there and get my <<m:1>> back!
Thanks for coming. We could have used you sooner, but there's no point dwelling on what might have been.
Siege weapons can make all the difference in battle. If you need some, talk to my assist here. He can sell you want you need.
This was a message from my brother. One I wasn't meant to survive. I feared this day would come.
What news do you bring?
I see you've been asking around, that's good. Do you know what you need to do?
I see you met Thane Oda Wolf-Sister.
I'm glad I'm out of that ridiculous cage.
The Stormfists won't take us by surprise again. You can be sure of that.
