I've been watching you, and you have been looking around this boat pretty well. What have you learned?
Have you any idea? Ooh, this is so exciting!
Ok, so what have you discovered and do you have any questions?
I hear you've been working with Thane Mera. How exciting!nnMight I ask what you've been doing? No? Very well, then.
The're alive! And they're not furry!nnSorry, Wild. I mean, they don't have tails. Let me start over .
Threads are falling into place again. The warp and weft align perfectly in the story!
You've started the story! I thought <<1>> lost in her own world by now. She must want you to play the part!
As I've already told the others, we must look for <<1>> soon, or there's no hope of finding her.nnWho will tell the Green Lady her sister's gone then? Who?
I saw you wreaking havoc among the Orcthane's troops. Most impressive!

The totem of Y'ffre is a thing of legend, with many tales woven into its essence. If you use it to fight the Worm Cult's creation, you may yet survive.nnSpinner Indinael is counting on you. I hope both of your stories will come to a safe conclusion.
The Worm Cult piled the spriggans' corpses like so much cordwood. Their disrespect knows no bounds.nnBurn what's left of the spriggans. You must deny the necromancers the heartwood.

Take down as many Worm Cultists as you like on your way through the cave! They deserve a thousand times more for what they've done!nnAs for the creature, use the totem of Y'ffre on it once it's weakened. If you don't, it'll just revive again.
May our humble offerings bring Sheor's mercy upon us. Then, we feast!
Use the shalk gland. It reacts violently with the roots!
You need to use the shalk glad to burn away these roots!
I need those gems! Quickly, now.
The Imperial has something he wants to say. I don't trust him.
Z'en would abandon me in my time of need? After all this, he gives me nothing?
I will mourn my lost friends and fellow workers for a long time.
The singing. The screaming. It was horrible.nnThe screaming, not the singing. I rather liked the singing.
I'm not sure we'll ever feel safe here again.
Who are you? How'd you get in here with weapons?
All this death, destruction. It has to stop.
He's gone. I can feel it. His presence faded when you struck him down.nnWe don't need to fear his tyranny any longer.
I will pray for you. I will pray for all of us.
If you wish to speak with Indinael, I suggest you hurry. Something is wrong.
That plant-murdering Worm just about broke my arm.

We're going to be famous! We'll have real support and proper recognition! Things are going to be much better for us from now on.nnThanks to you. And feel free to use the lift to get out of here whenever you're ready.

Best you do not think too hard about what's in that bottle. Just splash it on the hunters. Every splash saves a life. And don't be stingy. There's a lot more where that came from. nnIsn't that right, Cello? Oh yes it is!
This is now your story, where you saved Malabal Tor.
The Green Lady is quick, but the Silvenar has the eyes of the forest at his command.
Are you ready to begin the siege of Cradlecrush?
<<1>> was blinded by rage and remorse. He has fallen from the even path, into darkness.
Everything happened so quickly.
Whoever did this will pay!
Farewell.
Let's get out of this place!
Still you pursue me! I tire of your games.nnI will call the Hound to take your head as a prize. Begone, before he arrives!
The other spinners wait for you at the <<1>>.
I will be your guide on this journey.

You're right. This is going to work out. I love to go delving without a care, but Raynor can't stand it when everyone mocks him and doesn't take him seriously.nnI can understand it. Raynor deserves a little recognition.
Wonderful. These bear steaks will feed a lot of people. Did Old Ironclaw give you any trouble?
Why must I cook for the unrefined palate?
The prison's not perfectyet. But we have time, and Rilis isn't going anywhere.
Smoke fills the sky! From Nimalten to Shor's Stone, the people of the Rift know there's danger coming. Well done, my friend.
Greetings in his name. Always happy to see new faces join us!
So. It is finished.
I can't believe I slept through the attack.
The path is clear, friend of frond and leaf.
What is that stench? Is that coming from you? What did you do, roll around in a wolf den? No offense, but move downwind, please.
<Melril's eyes have glazed over, and his breath hitches. He is not long for Sovngarde.>
Show <<1>> what you brought back. Should wipe the smirk off his face.
As you can see, I am very busy here. Be on your way, please.
The High Kinsman must pay.
Areldur and I will tend to Imiril. Speak to Cirion.
Go to your king. And take the Dreamwalker with you, please.
Shame about the war. Best fishing I ever did was in Skyrim.
Well, we've had a bit of luck!nn<<1>> was sniffing around and found some of our props. If we can get the rest back, we won't have to skip our next show!
Don't worry about a thing. I've got everything planned out!
Y'ffre blessed us today. My wife's alive, and we're both back in Deepwoods.
All my fears are coming back, even stronger than before! But Sai needs me. I have to shake this off!nnAll right Titanborn, pull yourself together. You can do this.
Do you desire another philosophical discussion?
Alert the heralds. Irnskar's errand runner has returned.
Who are you? Where is <<1>>?
The Three Old Gods watch over this man and grant him a quick, painless journey from this place.
We'll always remember you here, friend. Kyne watch over you!
I'll give you a few minutes to get moving, then I'll see if I can sneak out of the compound. Hopefully, you'll create a large distraction by disrupting the binding stones.
When you disrupt the binding stones with the rune key, the Drublog will likely go berserk. I'll see if I can take a few of them out for you.nnI'll make it to the road before they get me, never fear.
You have the soul of Ysgramor and the heart of a giant-killer.nnThank you, friend! We'll always remember you.
Selgaard made it home right after you left. Thank you for entering the barrow in his stead.
It's too late! Fur crawls within my flesh!nnI don't want to die, but I can't live as a monster!
Collect my burial stones then meet me outside my tomb. The gathered stones may counter their necromantic spells.
I hope your light shines as brightly at Honrich Tower as it has here.
Are the geodes shattered? Please, release those poor souls.
This place is a slaughterhouse! What did you find?
Can't begin to make up for what the Reach bastards have done to my kin. They owe me for the blood paid today.
I accept the King's judgment. Do what you need to. I won't flee. You have my word.
At last. I'd begun to give up hope. Are you a friend to the Bosmer? I cannot see you clearly . Who are you?
The Ebonheart Pact is sealed and this threat to Skyrim has ended.nnPlease, go and tell my son. Tell him that the battle is won and  tell him about Fildgor.
I cannot stand my soul being trapped here any longer. Free me!
The storm atronachs congregate whenever the sphere is active for more than a few hours. How fortuitous they carry the thunderstones we need.
Events are spiraling out of control, and as the spinners say, we've "left the story."nnWithout you, neither I nor my ambassador would've gotten out of Jathsogur.
You saved Charadin. Bless you!
<Dalaneth looks peaceful in death, despite her many injuries.>
Seems you're worth something after all. Perhaps once the wards are unsealed, they'll consider you a stormwarden recruit.
While you're tracking down the thieves, I'll try to figure out what they took. They can't have made off with everything.
This disaster has convinced menever leave my library again. Fieldwork is for the young and foolish.

I can never repay you for all you've done. I should throw a grand feast and make you part of my personal guard, but there are still dangers to deal with.nnFildgor plans to desecrate my sister's spirit. That must not be allowed to happen.
They're expending a lot of power holding open those portals. Shut them down, and you'll draw Thallik out for sure.
Damn Worms! Driving them out will cost us dearly.nnAnd with all that we have accomplished, we still may not have the numbers to win this.
You dare approach me, mortal? I'll carve what's left of you into gaming bones!
You have made your decision. Majorn doesn't take such insults lightly. I expect that you won't have that long to regret your choice before Majorn destroys you.
You're covered in blood  does that mean you
You dare approach me, mortal? I will carve you into the tiniest of pieces, meat-sack!
Back already? My, you're rather fast  for an assistant.
You again? Got something interesting for me?
You've done well, my friend. I've been tracking your progress.

My friend, you've seen me through many trials and I'm grateful. But uniting my spirituality with the Green Lady's physicality is something I must do myself.nnThe celebration continues throughout the city. Enjoy yourself!
Not so loud! I don't want them to notice me.

You've got <<Amz:1>>? Good! Keep them close. I don't know what they're for, but they've got to be important.nnBut before that, you've got to defeat the Guardian of Silvenar. It patrols the bridge between here and the city.
Is it gone? Are there any more?
Is it gone? Are there any more?
Is there something else I can tell you?
You can't kill me! Don't you know who I am?
The future rushes toward us at break-neck speed! Quickly, you must continue your mission. Do not worry about me!
The triumvirate is free, and our energies can no longer be used against the rightful rulers of this city.nnGo to the Silvenar, now. He will tell you what needs to be done to preserve this moment.
This looks like a back entrance, but it's bolted shut. I think these items around the door frame are part of a puzzle lock. Look around. Maybe there's a clue to the right sequence nearby.
Greetings. What brings you to my pier in the middle of this disaster?
Watch out! Don't you know the Houndsmen are listening?
By the Eight, you are an annoying one!nnDo you have a crush on me or something? Let me speak to my friend here. In peace. That means alone.
I'll coordinate my tale with Spinners Einrel and Caerllin. Meanwhile, you must get to the Green Lady!nnWe'll take care of getting the Silvenar inside the city. A fitting climax to a terrifying tale.
Ah, the sweet smell of Maormer boats on fire. I quite like the aroma.nnSince you're here, may I conclude you've finished your task?
This makes no sense. Who would attack us? Maybe it was the Orcthane and his Stormfist Brigade!
Search for the <<C:1>> on the ship. I'll meet you there, once I've recovered my gear.
I'll make sure the Pact knows of your courage. The fight against Stral. Epic.
I'm afraid you just missed Commander Yjarnn. Again.nnHe was in a hurry. He always seems to run when everyone else around here just saunters.
Hello, friend! How long has it been? You remember Rigurt the Brash, leader of the Glorious Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange? nnIt is good to see you again. You are just in time to help.
Welcome to Voljar's Meadery. Please excuse the mess.
I've had enough of this pit of Oblivion. I'm going home.
I heard that you've been hard at work.nnA powerful troll for the Argonians? Really? That's quite remarkable.
That went amazingly well. I think.
Things return to normal so slowly these days. Is there really a time when everything is as we imagine?
Get out there. Thallik must be put down.
You're back. I hope the skeever hunt went well. Killed all the zombies, made us safe?
The spinners will weave your actions into the story of the Bosmer. I'll see to that myself.nnI'm the Green Lady. They'll listen.
I'm honored to be here, but to be honest, I mostly can't wait until the parties start.
I don't see the bard with you.
We should leave this place. Let the forest have it.
You're not wanted here, outsider. For all we know, you're carrying the plague.
You will swim in the waters of victory. I smell it.
I heard you went through the portal and defeated <<1>>.
I heard you went through the portal and defeated <<1>>.
I'm not sure how I'm supposed to convince the people in Nimalten everything's going to be all right. There's a damned ghost giant roaming the land  things are not going to be all right.
What brings you to my hall? You don't look in need of a thane's help. And if you are with Aera, I am not in need of her help, either.

Do you fully understand what it is you recovered from Sancre Tor? Even without being able to use it, the Amulet of Kings is literally priceless. You would bankrupt kingdoms who would take it only for symbolic value.nnDon't get any ideas.
The Thane holds court in the manor hall.
Are you ready to go?
Good work. I've been gathering intelligence, and have good news.
Thanks for helping us get rid of the Orcthane's thugs.
Go on, before Sadri disappears for good.
I'm so happy Asgi made it through this ordeal safely.
What's that smell? It's awful.
Told you something bad was going to happen.nnI didn't want you to walk into this trap alone. So I followed you. Good thing, too.
Thanks for helping us. Have some stew. I just made a fresh pot.
The murderer propped Betar up. They wanted us to see him. I'm thinking this was a warning.
You're here to speak to Hallfrida, aren't you? Why do you disturb me? The girl is wild. She needs a strong hand to discipline her.
You! You are the creature who stole my sword?nnTime enough to deal with you after this is over. In the meantime, out of my sight!
My friend! I would swear we only spoke days ago. I can see by the look on your face you know of Nimalten's dark times.
I once held a sword and shield. I protected those I cared for in battle.nnOn this throne I feel helpless.
I had nothing to do with this. I was forced to help them.nnIt wasn't supposed to happen like this.
I can see the smoke! Now everybody knows the danger they face. Blood for the Pact!
The matrons are awake! It was much easier to enter, but I still sense  danger.
I'll be fine. Help Voranil!
I don't seem to be making much progress.
target: Non mi sembra di fare molti progressi.

source: Did you retrieve my silk?
My silk! Excellent.
You get that blade, and I'll see Thorulf hung from the highest point in the hall!
I've worked my whole life to achieve this. Thank you for honoring me with your presence.
You're alive! I thought they might have taken you too .
We're going to get the fort up and running again. My scouts report that there are still Stormfist troops in the area.
We succeeded where that withered root failed, comrade.nnHere. I will open a portal for you to return.
Why would you do that? We could have ridden out the entire plague on that supply.
You are back. Impressive. Aelif still cannot see what the godless Dwarves might have had.nnWhat would they have that <<1>> would want?
You are back. Impressive. Aelif still cannot see what the godless Dwarves might have had.nnWhat would they have that <<1>> would want?
Stendarr's mercy! You've returned! But where is <<1>>?
Well, this trip was a disaster.
Snorrvild and I have learned our lesson. No more wilderness for us. I think we'll stick to in-town adventures from now on.
We should really stop meeting like this.
It's always nice to meet new people in exciting places!
Many thanks to you, my friend. If you ever find an artifact that needs deciphering, well, ask my sister.
The Worms won't stand a chance. I hope some of my men still live down there.
Read the notes. You'll understand them better than I will. Plus, I'm dying.
Go quickly! There isn't much time!
If I were flesh again, I'd bring the fight to the Worm Cult!
Listen to the hengekeeper. <<1>> depends on her.
I hear them. The matrons, the leaves, the drops of rain. The whole forest, all around us.nnAnd over it all, I can hear the Green Lady.
That was good work back there. My superiors will be pleased.
Welcome Ghorgarz, champion of Bargam!
I should've expected trouble. The wind hasn't smelled right since that cat became Merric's constant companion.
Head to Pinepeak Caverns. Only you can safeguard Hakra, liege-lord.
You'd better get out of here. You've made enemies here.
Enough dwelling on what I wish had been. We must deal with what is.
You said the undead were taken care of. And Thorulf? Where's that bastard?
Is someone there? What's going on? I can't see!
Had any luck with the song, my new friend? Remember, I'll meet you at the manor when you've learned what you need to.
Are you ready to go back to your secret hiding spot?
Good, you're here. Ready to help the guild on another important mission?
Take the four points around the fort. Once you raise the banner, soldiers will rally to help you.
Ah, you've returned. Do you have the second book?
From what I could see, things were a little exciting in there.nnBut you got the book, correct?
I always love a deluded mind. It's so much like a work of art.
You've returned! Do you have the book?
They've turned you against me, haven't they? You're one of them, now! Get out! Leave, I say! You'll never have it! It's mine!
Well met! Let me buy you a drink, my newfound friend.
If you need something, please talk to Master Benus. I have a lot of work to do.
If you have something to say, make it quick. I'm in the middle of negotiations.
She's waiting for you at the Evermore Guildhall in Bangkorai. Good luck, comrade.
Honestly, fear is the only thing that will get <<1>> to give up that ruby.
Father, why are you still here? Haven't you done enough?
They'll never take me alive, Jarl. Don't worry about me.
This tune is for everyone listening from the Ashlands. Raise your flagons, Dark Elves!
Do whatever Sheogorath tells you. We need him to give us the next book.
Why did my guards let you in here? I need to have a talk with them about the meaning of the word "guard."nnGo away, commoner. If you want to meet with the King or  I, petition your Jarl.
I wonder if that old horse would make it to Winterhold? I could set out tonight
Nimalten reminds me of Bleakrock. All these good people, oblivious to danger. If only we could have protected my husband and son.nnHave you learned anything?
I'm close.
The Worm Cult is becoming terribly powerful.
Well done, my friend. May <<1>> never again arise to haunt us!
I've seen what the Reach do to people. I begged Vigrod to let me loose on them. <<1>> can undo some of what they've done, but I want to slit some throats.
Place <<mz:1>> in the holders, then we can enter Abamath's ruins.
She's preparing a ritual space at the Riften Guildhall in The Rift. I'll see you there, Adept. We're so close!
I will protect <<1>> with my life.nnWalk in radiance, my friend.
The honored Queen Nurnhilde has spoken on your behalf and granted you entrance to Sovngarde.nnStep into the column of light and get on with your business.
The heat will seal the words firmly in the mammoth flesh. I hope so, at least.
Did you get them? Did you rip apart those Daedra and take their hearts?
Leading the charge as always, eh?nnWe've lost many soldiers trying to take these caves. The Worms wield barrels filled with a flammable liquid. If you see barrels ahead, be wary.
May the waters protect you. You will succeed.nnRemember, not all foes must be fought. Use your stealth and your wits to avoid fights. Save your strength for the true enemy, Sinmur.
Have you retrieved the shards of Wuuthrad? Without them, Sinmur will be extremely difficult to defeat.nnIf you don't have the shards, I suggest you recruit friends to aid you.
I'm getting better?
Thank you for collecting these. I'll give them to the families of the fallen.
How many more will die today? Will any of us live to see our homes again?
You have done the Mages Guild a great service. We shall use Sanctuary to continue our studies in peace and solitude.
Stay back. This one's dangerous.
I tried  I saved the civilians trapped by the Orcs, but a big one came from behind. I'm finished, my friend.nnHow'd you fare? Better?

The captain's men are as disgusted with her as I am. With the townsfolk willing to testify against her, the Fists of Thalmor will have no choice but to cashier her.nnShe'll be locked up until we receive word from Elden Root.
I do hope Lord Sheogorath will appreciate his gift.
Nice.
<This Dark Elf woman wears Worm Cultist garb. From the claw marks, it appears she was mauled to death by sabre cats. A look through her pack reveals a blood-stained journal.>
The invaders crossed the bridge! They've taken over the entire town!
We're going to die! We're all going to die!
The captain won't tolerate your presence for long. Leave while you can!
We're not waiting any longer! Velyn Harbor's our town and we're taking it back!
Hasn't your kind done enough!

Listen, if we work quickly, we can cut our losses! Those thieves didn't nab everything. One of the rotmeth bladders is ready to turn, but we're short on a few critical seasonings.nnYou're good with animals. Maybe you can help me out?
Together we'll storm Fallowstone Hall and teach those bastards a lesson they'll never forget!
Good luck in there! I don't envy you, so once this is over the drinks are on me!
I was in the brewery when someone struck me on the back of my head. I must've been out for several minutes.nnWhoever hit me is still upstairs with the sacred brew. We've got to stop him!
I knew Sees-All-Colors was responsible.
How did you find me? Never mind. That's not important.nnThe Sigil. You have to find the Sigil.
It didn't work. I wasn't able to shield myself from the nightmares.nnShe is  she is gone. I couldn't save her.
She's dead. I can't believe she's dead. What about the Sigil?
Hey there, friend. If you're interested in joining the Fighters Guild, just say the word.
Interested in additional training in guild techniques?nnI've a few things for sale, but only if you have the appropriate standing in the guild.
Small guild representation out here at Fort Amol, isn't it? It's good to see another member in the area.
Good to see more guild members in the area. We don't have much of a hall here, but members are always welcome.
Leave me. I told you what you wanted to know.nnYou'll see. You'll see how the lizard fails. Just you wait. I know what I'm talking about.
What are you, my mother?nnGet out of here. You're ruining my me time.
What can Laughs do for you? You need something special?
I'll never forget what you and Stormy did for me.nnYou saved me. Both of you.
So, are you going to give me the salts or what? I really need them.
Ah, you again. Veldrana's been regaling us with your heroics. Captain Viveka led a Riften Guard patrol out here. We're following up.
Ahh. I'm getting the feeling back in my toes. Ow! Pins and needles! Pins and needles!
Remarkable. I'm not easily impressed, but you've done it.nnUricantar, on the other handwhat a waste. Truly.
Without your help here, the tale of Andewen in Ezduiin would have gone very differently, I think.nnGood luck in your travels.
You are very kind to help, though you do not seem to know Valeguard's importance. Perhaps <<1>> can explain things for you?
The souls must be releasedone way or another.
This one never should have come here. Jiluza misses the sands of Dune.
To think I was excited about coming here. I want to impress Telenger. But I'm not sure my soul is a price I'm willing to pay.
Ezduiin holds no more fascination for me. I wish to be rid of these ruins.
Every stone here unnerves me. I keep expecting a spirit to peer around each corner.
Leave me alone!
Time's slipping away, friend. If you want to beat my record you need to get out there with that bow.nnTalking to me isn't going to help you catch rabbits.
Sure, you could use normal, non-magical, absolutely regular arrows.nnOr you could use exciting arrows. Fiery arrows. Arrows that get to go boom!
Please  we need to stop the Maormer .

This invasion is over! Without the ability to signal their ships, the Maormer won't be able to navigate the shallows. They'll turn around or find themselves swimming back to Pyandonea.nnAll of Auridon is in your debt. Well done!
Well, you made short work of that little task. My vengeance is complete.nnI thank you, and I owe you a debt. Perhaps we'll see each other again sometime.
You can do it! Beat that lizard at his own game!
You do me a great honor. I miss my three daughters terribly. I'm not whole without them.nnBut you give me hope.
Pleased to meet you, I'm sure. These damnable Maormer are not the most charitable of hosts.
Didn't expect to see a friendly face. Get me out of here.
Maormer scum. They took us by surprise. Did the Captain send you?
Please find my friends' bodies and burn them before they rise as vampires!
You risked everything to help me. I won't forget it.
Incredible! Did you see that? Unfortunate that the crystal lattice was destroyed in the process, but it served its purpose well.
Don't suppose you're bringing any reinforcements, are you?
Did you see her? She tried to kill me! nnColonwe is an ancestral spirit that haunts this grove. She's always been a mischievous one, but I've never seen her so violent!
Thanks to you and <<1>>, these people will be able to find their eternal rest.
My sisters and I are ready to aid you.
Hmm. You look familiar. Have we met before?
My Sister of Waves lingers just ahead. Go. Find her.
We will make ready to face the lamia queen, and meet you when our spells are ready.
Destroy that thing before it kills the captain!
I've never felt such pain! Ugh, the Maormer are little better than animals!
The Worm Cult might've summoned Mauloch without your intervention. We're all grateful for what you did to stop them.
The Worm Cult sought the Blood of Mauloch? Praise Y'ffre you were here to stop them!
Be strong. The fate of our ancestors' eternal souls rests in your hands now.
<Golun was stabbed repeatedly until he died.>
<<1>> brought the shard you retrieved into the ruins for the final battle.nnWith only one shard, you have little chance of defeating Sinmur by yourself.
Despite our losses, we can still turn the tide here!
With you at our side, we'll take back the Hall or die trying!
Please watch over Ande. Don't let anything happen to her!
Any luck?
Andewen got us out of there. She has the scales of Auri-El!
Good luck in there.
I wasn't here long enough to know <<1>>. Her reputation brought me here.
These Worms should never have crawled up from below.
Sir! Glad I found you. The Silvenar told us to keep eyes out for you.nnWe're kind of in the frying pan here.
Do not stay your hand. The curse ends with my death as easily as any other way.nnKill me.
I knew something was up with these guards. An actual member of the First Auridon Marines has shown up. He wanted to speak with you.
Get going, Arrow. If Ash has asked your aid, you've no time to waste chatting with me.
Excellent work! They had it coming.
The camp's not far from here. I doubt the cultists will simply let you take one.nnThey never dared enter Treehenge before. I wonder what changed?
Some of the villagers may be inside their homes, but most are in the market square. Vadda'ra hopes you can live with yourself for doing this.
A necromancer leads the cultists, sacrificing them to reach my tomb. Each death strengthens the spell he's ready to cast.
I really don't know much about how to get inside Silvenar. I only arrived here with the Silvenar a few hours ago.nnHmm  that whole naming thing could get a bit confusing, couldn't it?
Oh, still around? You're a dedicated merchant!
A lighthouse is just a tower of stone. Towers can be rebuilt.
Bloody parchment in your hands. Does that mean ?
Can I help you?
You're a gentle sort. Thank you. I'll see Yiri's taken care of.nnYou deal with those Worm Cult bastards.
I know our sound isn't "together" yet, but it will be! See you in Silvenar!
Now you'll all see? My new friend here is going to finish you off!
Those drums are the best I've ever had. Now that you've found us, please find them!
We can't perform without instruments! Please find them!
Music brings people together on many different levels, doesn't it?
Well, well. Seems you're the one I should've concerned myself with all along.nnI've got my orders, no thanks to those Khajiit. They'll get their just reward soon enough.
We knocked the giants from their perches!
You see? There were too many. Look what they've done  what they're capable of doing! Monstrous!
She's made it to the crypts? Hmm. Well, at least now she's surrounded by family.
Her Majesty can handle herself, but she can also be reckless. Don't leave her side!
When we spoke last, I said your tale would be forever remembered. It seems our memories must grow longer if we are to keep up with your exploits.
Don't let death and destruction discourage you, friend. For the right coin, this one can make your day.
Fool! Take the shard. It will never profit you.
Can't believe they won't let an old man drink in peace.
This Amulet is incredibly important. We will protect it until we are ready to use it.
You're working with Tovisa? I hope you have a plan.
I just want to go home. Get some rest. Read a book.
Have you located my commander?
This time we should burn that giant to ashes. And then scatter the ashes to the winds.nnHave you spoken with Vigrod yet?
I hope that's the last we ever see of Sinmur. Vigrod's been looking all over for you.
Telenger is amazing, isn't he? I'd do anything to get his recommendation.
Honor and praise to you. It's always been my dream to work with Telenger. He's quite brilliant. And handsome!nnSuch a shame Ezduiin has been such a disappointment.
Telenger's recommendation is a powerful force within the guild. I only hope one day I can earn it.
I'd heard being Telenger's assistant was dangerous. But this!
Everyone here only cares about impressing Telenger. It's all Ejukki hears day in and day out.
I hope someday Telenger will look upon me as he does Andewen. I want to prove myself.nnI just don't want to end up like Uricantar.
May your step be silent and fall in shadow, friend.
There you are. Vigrod wants to talk to you, right away.
Are you insane? Can't you see the town is under attack?
You did it! The whole line speaks of your service. The bodies we've got out here will make sure the Daedra stay bottled up in Firsthold.nnThank you.
We've got a dozen more strong bodies on the line, traveler! Thank you for bringing word of our troubles to Skywatch.
Ah, at last. Queen Ayrenn is eager to speak with you.
Do you think I should change my hair color? I'm thinking of something in a pink or green.
My agents tell me that three new souls have joined the celebration.
Enough! I'm no match for an Ebonheart brute.
Fine. You win. Give me the goblet.
No more! I'll drink it.
My men and I will try to keep the locals out of the area. There are few things more dangerous than ancestral spirits on a rampage.
Word of advice, friend. Never trust a necromancer.nnIf you absolutely have to, think hard, and then walk the other way.
You got here just in time.nnBut I know you didn't come in with the investigation team. Who are you?
You shouldn't have a hard time looking for a fight around here. nnLuck.
I'm still dead, aren't I? I hoped it was just a bad dream. I sense I still have one more role to play, though.
This audience needs to drink more.
I'm bored. There's too much chatter and not enough rhythm.
I love a good crowd, but there needs to be music!
I'll never be able to face Bar-Neeus again, curse him. His generosity has saved us and we'll rebuild. Only when I can repay him will my shame be lessened. Damn him, and you!
If anyone can retrieve No-Name's precious package, it's you!nnWonderful, courageous, admirable you!
Damned undead. If there's anything I can't stand it's a Stars-damned vampire.
Ah, you're back. Good. Sorry, just trying to stay on my feet.
Need to see this woman. No time to talk.
You did it! Congratulations!
Ah, it is a sun-blessed day, no? Is there something I can interest you in?
How goes the search? Still searching, yes? Hmm.
Thought I might make it to Vulkhel Guard, but I just couldn't go any farther.
<<1>> is free! You're so kind to help me.
Will the killers come back? Are we safe here? I can't stop shaking, I'm so afraid!
You've returned! And the bards, stupid though they may be, are alive!
Poor Queen. Razum-dar can't imagine her sitting out the fight willingly. Her retinue must have held her down to keep her from entering the fray.
You've done it! The rest of the lady's entourage has gone on ahead. Did you deal with the mad man?
My friends are in cages in the Worm Cult camp. Will you rescue them? One of the cultists must have the key!
Once again, you've pulled my arse out of the fire. I owe you a round, maybe two, next time you're in Riften.
Dark rumors in town. Too many dark rumors.
Have you heard the rumors of cultists about? Dark times, indeed.
Good luck in your travels, my friend. I'm sure the Nords of Skyrim are grateful for your presence. Just as grateful as I am.
You're lucky you're not a Daedra. I may be an innkeeper, but that doesn't mean I can't adequately protect myself!
The Eight save us! We're surrounded! We're all going to die out here!
Full Moon. This one had errands to run today. Jiyya was lucky enough to be outside the city when High Kinlady Estre arrived.
This might be Iduthal's last mug of amber ale  if the Daedra haven't destroyed this one's supply. nnTuinvitar said there's no way he'd let the Dremora get to it. The fool.
Thank you. Thank you so much. I can think again.
The Thane will set you straight. Kyne guide your path.
That's wonderful! Did you swoon? I would have swooned.nnMy collection is complete! And I have an autograph! Um  could you ask about a second book?
There's no hope for it! The city's lost. Might as well start looking to move to Skywatch.
They killed my husband! Those bastards .
What are you doing! The Prophet's opened the way, get going!
Thank you. You've spared my life. I can never repay you. But I swear on my magic, I'll never truck with Daedra again.
Hey there.
What are you doing in my home? Don't you know who I am?
Sorry, help you? I've got a lot of work to do around here.
With the barriers down, Estre will be the next to fall.
Thanks to you, we were able to destroy the wards. I wish you the same luck against High Kinlady Estre.
We've done it! Thank the Eight you showed up.
You've done it! I only wish I could have been of assistance.
You're not one of them. Need your help. Not for meI'm doomedbut the others.
I'd like to catch up with the Maulborn and give them what they gave the merchants.
How many lives does this Vox have to take? Diiril. The merchants. She needs to pay for what she's done.
What do you want? If it's a favor, I have no time to spare right now.
It's so cold. Can barely move. Never get out of here.nnNot sure I want to.
Mara watches over us all. Everything happens according to her plan, though we often don't see it.
Yes, what is it? I'm a busy man.
The afflicted found their way up here while you were inside. But we cut them down. Every one of them.
You almost feel sorry for them. Flesh rotting. Blood boiling.nnYep. Almost.
No traces of plague must survive. The bodies have to burn.
Ayrenn's healers have seen to me. I'm alive, thanks to you.
<Velatosse stares at you, her eyes dead inside.>
Auri-El watches over you. You have my thanks for your victory here today.

The Battlereeve tells me Estre is dead. I mourn her loss. nnShe is the past. And you, our future. Your service to our people has been exemplary. You have proven yourself a valuable asset to the Aldmeri Dominion.
Having second thoughts?
Yeah?
Filthy Daedra running about our city. It's a disgrace.
Thane Vofknir is a generous man. I'm sure he'll set you on the path.
We're here for your protection. If you're not sick, get out of here.
Nothing to see here. Move along.
Isn't she beautiful? Where has she been all my life? nnWe'll be together. Forever.

She has passion, eh? I'll dispatch a messenger tonight. I know a graveyard that's perfect for our rendezvous. nnAnd there's a desanctified shrine to a Daedric Prince nearby. The acoustics are incredible. I should do a reading there someday.
My wife and I specialize in weapons. I'd love to show you our wares, only  I can imagine you'd understand why we don't have any right now.
Curse Estre. I knew she was trouble the moment she came to Firsthold. Now look at what she's doing to our beautiful city!
High Kinlady Estre is out of her mind. Worshipping Mehrunes Dagon and corrupting High Kinlord Rilis. The Queen won't have it. Battlereeve Urcelmo is already here. He'll see to Estre's demise.
I'm lucky to have made it out alive. If the Marines hadn't shown up, I'd be face down in the ground by now.
Nothing ever comes of worshipping Daedric Princes. Especially one like Mehrunes Dagon. I can't imagine this bodes well for Estre.
Burakgum never thought it was possible for Firsthold to fall.
Be careful. High Kinlady Estre sure has made a mess of Firsthold. I just hope High Kinlord Rilis is all right.
If Queen Ayrenn didn't care so much about her precious Aldmeri Dominion, this never would have happened.
How could you side with that traitor? Unbelievable!
It is done, and we must walk this dark road together. As the scrolls foretold.
Oh, my son! I can't believe it. After everything I did to protect him .
Where am I? What happened?
Have you seen <<1>>? He stepped out for a moment. He said he'd be right back. I hope the undead don't hurt him.
<The statue looks very lifelike.>
I wish I'd been there to help you kill Gullveig. I would've enjoyed that.
It is good to feel the flow of life around me once more.
Speak with Captain Viveka soon. She's impatient to leave.
I see a hero standing before me. You have risen high in my estimation today.
Thank you again.
Were you telling the truth? Merormo has trafficed with Daedra?
We sure showed those bastards, eh?
I hope that the merchant's promises are good and he keeps other Hlaalu away from here.
Are you sick? You seem to have lost a lot of weight.
The ghosts are gone, but I'm still woried about my brother Nilus.
Hey. Name's Mininaire. I have a proposition for you.
<<1>> warned me about the danger this place posed with all of the Maormer about. Poor lass! She deserves better.nnIf you deal with those Broken Coast bastards, I'll see she gets it.
What do you want? I'm not leaving till I get what I came for.
Thank the Eight I found you! Teldur has betrayed us!
Please. No more questions. Just leave me alone.
You go on. We'll see you at the Withered Tree.
One of the men in the crew caught. Whatever this is. Thanks for sticking around.
Still around? Good for you.
I comend you for your valor.
Get away from me, cat. I don't know what sort of disease lives in your fur, and I don't want to find out.
I need to make medicine for Barothlas. Explore the valley and find out what's going on there. Maybe someone below knows where the city went.
Oh, it's you again. Did you show good Jorald here that ring you found? I'm sure he would be pleased to know you gave the bandits what they deserved.
These people are lunatics. As soon as Barothlas can walk, Jarakh will return to Velyn Harbor.nnThere is no profit to be had here. Perhaps next year.
No telling what'll happen if the cultists complete their ritual. Please help us stop it!
Back already? What about <<1>>? She must still be in the Smokefrost Peaks.
Nice! That'll show 'em!
Get in there and take out those cultists. I don't want to see what happens if they complete their ritual.
What are you doing here? You should be meeting <<1>> at the dragonshrine.
We have to stop the ritual!
You have my thanks for helping Raerana. You're always welcome at The Withered Tree!nnAnything I can get you?
We didn't wait long enough after sealing the tears outside. Or maybe there are two Daedroth! Let's wait for the second to come forth, and then the city is sure to follow.
Do what you can. Heldil needs your help.
Honor and praise. I'll need you to speak with Watch Captain Astanya. nnJust follow the docks to the west.
Fair day, and welcome to Vulkhel Guard. I need you to speak with Watch Captain Astanya.nnFollow the docks to the northeast. Can't miss her.
Welcome, traveler. What brings you to the city?
Welcome to Vulkhel Guard. We're asking all visitors to register their arrival in the city. Security for the Queen, don't you know.
They're all doomed, and I'm next!
You again? Shouldn't you be off running errands somewhere?
Well? If you're here to end me, do it and be done. I'm tired of waiting.
Hurry, traveler. My comrades at the lighthouse. They can't hold out forever. nnAnd who knows when the Daggers will decide to off the Orc?
I see it in your faceyou have word of my husband. Please tell me!
<You would almost swear this statue could move.>
The Sentinels are connected. If we destroy one, the others will also be blinded for a time.
Estrethe High Kinlady herself? I can't believe it, though I've seen it now with my own eyes.
Grab a mug and get to drinking!
Let me guess, that handiwork on those houses was your doing?
Ah, peace at last. Or as peaceful as the Rift can be nowadays. I feared the giants would never leave us alone.
I'm very worried about my cooks. I hope you can find whatever's causing the trouble!
I have to admit, I'm impressed. Cool like the scales of Auri-El, you are.nnGood luck with the captain.
You're no guard. Thank the Stars. Quickly, we don't have much time.
Explain yourself. What are you doing here?
This town is rotten, down to the roots. Like a Full Moon, the Eyes of the Queen stare down.
Make your way to Tanzelwil at your own pace. Seek out my entourage when you arrive. They'll be able to direct you to me.nnAnd good luck, to us both, on the road.
Ah, back again. Answering riddles for Iroda. Want some help with this one?
Raz needs to report our success here. Her Majesty will be pleased.
You should continue to listen to the story of our village. <<1>> has more to tell.
Do you know what happened to my husband Urynnar? Has he been cured?
Thanks again for hunting down my crew. Ungrateful louts.
A Maormer infestation of Auridon could be very, very bad. Anala hates to think of how bad this could be.
Oof. Damn that wine.
Do you have something to say?

You are a bag of miracles, my friend. We are fortunate the Cult did not enthrall you, though perhaps your will would have overcome them anyway.nnAs for the Obsidian HuskI destroyed it while you did battle with Theran.
I warned her. I told her I'd never been on a ship before. I think she was fine with my work.nnUntil I threw up on her boots.
I hope all is well. What brings you to back to Fallowstone?
Ivarstead is quite a trek. But if you want the coin, start walking. Ha!

Well, I have to say, I'm rather shocked you actually completed the contract with all your bumbling. Well, congradualtions, you made it through without getting caught, that should earn you a sweet roll.
This one imagines you may have some questions. What can Raz tell you?
Please head to the ritual site. No telling what they're up to!
Have you talked to <<1>>? She's been looking for you.
<Its empty>
The finest weapons in all the Dominion. Forged right here in Mathiisen. nnHot off the anvil. If you will.
Step away from the house, please. The Canonreeve does not want her things disturbed.
Thank you for rescuing me!
So. How'd it go?
I've always hated spiders, but I think today proved that squashing them can be extremely gratifying.nnAt any rate, you've been a great help. Two-Blades will probably want to thank you, too.
It's up to you and me, friend!
You turned a crushing defeat into resounding victory, my friend. The Fighters Guild lost many today, but thanks to you, it was not for nothing.nnSpeak with Two-Blades when you are able.
Do  do you have them?
I've begun to hear rumors. They say there weren't many survivors. They say my  my father was killed.nnHe should have taken this more seriously. I  I can't believe he's gone.
From your look, I think you climbed the stairs to the Throat of the World. Did you find the herb?
I've heard things have calmed down a bit around here.
I can't believe you killed the giant. Really? Wow, uh, that's great.
Nice to see a new face in town. Be careful though. Lots of travelers have been disappearing lately.
I've been watching you, and you've been talking to just about everyone in therel. What have you learned?
Welcome to the Withered Tree. Good luck getting any actual help around here.
Thanks for the daggers, they'll fetch a nice price. I'll be in touch when I have another job for you.
Took your time, didn't you? Did you get the daggers?
Ow. Damn those Veiled Heritance!
Thank the Divines, I am not a dead man.
Don't you have someplace to be?
I can't stop worrying.
Those bugs are in the hay. All over the place. Go get them!
I'm not taking any more guild money. They want to kill one of their own, they can do it themselves.
Managed to bag my Ranger! And Cariel here has been telling me about your exploits.
If you're going to hang around, pull up a chair and buy us a round.
Defeat Ulfnir, then search him. We must get that crown!
My friends! I'm so pleased zombies didn't eat your faces!
Seems like Ankur might not have messed up this time. You just might work out.
I'm glad to see that business at Skuldafn's dealt with, but a soldier's duty is never done. The Rift needs your help.
Rescue, at last!
Ah, you've found my drunken Nords. I'll take them off your hands. Lead them back out.
<Malsia must have set Solvar aflame when he attacked her.>
The fish have stopped biting for some reason.
Thanks for the help. When the brew's done, I'll let you lick the foam off the ichor!
You must excuse us, we were just talking about the Queen's upcoming speech.
I'm sorry, I was just speaking with the High Kinlady. And now you've interrupted us. Excuse us, please?
Enjoying the city, I hope? Apologies if the others are a bit distracted. Everyone's on edge today.
This one hopes your new souvenir comes in handy.
So you're back! If this means you have what Mom wants, then I'd talk to her right away.
Hrmph. Feels like the dead have settled down some. I'm sure that won't last.
Please, lead me out of here.
Palith will come to forgive me in time. I may not ever forgive Eranamo.
Thank you. Thank you for sparing my brother's life.
I never want to see this place again.
I shouldn't have left the village, but I had to know if my daughter's alive.nnNow I don't know if I'll live long enough to see her again.
Thank the moons, we're not too late. I hope she still has enough strength to drink.
I know it's not much. But we wanted you to have this sack of supplies. Thank you!
Good luck. If you need us, the Marines have your back.
I only hope you're not too late.
That vile witch. I never liked her.
Bastards! Tall, pale, knife-eared bastards!
So. Did you finish your tour of our little school?
Remember, it's fine if the Redguard see you burning the boats; we want them to attack the Wood Orcs.nnOf course, that does mean you'll have to fight your way free of them, so be careful.
Nothing but trouble since them Redguards got here. Trouble! Stealing, conniving, ugly brutes.nnI hope you gave them what for!
You're a lucky recruit. The Veiled Queen herself will be making a speech in support of the cause. You'll be able to see her firsthand!nnAssuming you survive the trials.
Let's get this dispatch back to Aldcroft.
Gorak may be ready one day, but today is not that day.

Oraneth is dead, the ritual broken, yet evil still stirs here. There is a darkness, growing from the earth below, sprouting from a seed of death.nnWe have failed. The darkness is coming, with no one to control it .
Two of my scouts came back. Who was the traitor?
I'll see you dead for this!
Don't leave me here! They'll kill me!
If only my mother could see me now!
Don't lose any sleep over me. The Covenant isn't nearly as bloodthirsty as they say. I hope.
No! Nurad is  This one does not know where these supplies came from. Do not hurt Nurad!
I'd love to interrupt my lesson, but the instructor looks down on slothfulness.
Can I help you with anything?
Is there a reason you've interrupted my practice?
Well done!
Please leave me alone!
Such grace! Such poise! This one thinks you were a dancer in another life, yes?nnThe challenge of skill is complete. My treasures are yours to peruse.
Welcome, student.nnStudy hard and you'll do well, I'm sure.
Yummy bread. Enjoy it.
An impressive time. You've passed the Veil's trial of endurance.
Mara's heart, you've done good work here. Little wonder Razum-dar trusts you.
You took the wind out of Helane's sails, for sure. No one's ever crossed her that badly before!
Well done! You've proven you have a well-honed mind.
Took them long enough to send reinforcements.
She just wants to get out of here.
Hircine's Hunters can exist on both the physical plane and the spirtual one.nnThey penetrated the Silvenar's mind when he tried to discover the half-forgotten memory you're searching for.
You're a full member now. And you're in luck. The Veiled Queen herself will be speaking to the cause.
What were you thinking, coming in here after me? The Bloodthorn will escape!
I'm so happy to have Len back, safe and sound. He said you found him in the mine.
Feeble pup, I'd break you. Run along.
<You notice the nearly invisible seam of a circular disk at the center of the stone.>
That's close enough, stranger. Why do you approach Deepwoods?
Dame Clarique filled us in on what happened. I wish we could have gone in there with you instead of that bandit.
My brother Bernard and his family are coming to live in Daggerfall. He'll miss Deleyn's Mill, but it's safer inside the walls of the city.
We can't trust these conniving sneak-thieves to keep their end of a bargain.
It seems my little cave-in did the trick. Look, the prison is barely guarded.
I left my father to help the Eagle's Brook survivors. I was determined to make sure the Red Rooks wouldn't profit from more murder and mayhem.
I thank you, my friend. It's time we finish this. The Huntsman has killed too many and brought too much grief to my people.nnPlease make your way to the city of Silvenar. I could use your help.
The shrine is in the middle of the village. The lady's grace is embodied in the green which shelters the stone.
Move along.
Ha! You've got to take the small victories where you can, in this place.
About damn time, I say. Now, I just need an axe and I'll put a few Daedra in the ground before they get me.
It's a start, but I'd rather put this pick into a Daedra skull and then feast on its heart.nnWhat?
Best of luck. Do check in now and again, won't you?
There's a temple to Sanguine out in the swamps. You'd have to be strange in the head to go there on purpose.
I've lived in Stormhold my whole life. Don't understand why all the newcomers make such a big deal out of having to live with Argonians.
I heard you were at Hatching Pools when the Bosmer attacked. I'm glad you were. And I'm glad I wasn't.
It worries me to think of the Dominion watching us from those ruins on the hill. I'm glad you rooted them out.
Come no closer! Why do you approach Deepwoods?
Not many walk these roads lately. What brings you to Deepwoods?
We've retaken the Cove! By Mara! nnOw.
The slaves are armed and the uprising has begun. We may yet escape this place!
Look at our town. So much destruction. So much work to do.
You're a real live person, aren't you? I thought I was all alone out here. I bet you came from that city over there.nnCould you help me, please?
Phynaster guide your path.
Are you with the Marines? What happened?

I can see Raynor through this observation window, but he can't hear me. It must be the spell  and I bet the spell didn't affect me because I'm not attuned to whatever catalyst controls the magicka matrix.
We were too late. Too late.
I could sure use a mead right about now, but I need to keep a clear head. Otherwise we'll never break this enchantment.

I sense your uncertainty. There is a darkness weighing upon your mind that only serves to deepen your despair.nnFear not. The roots of the Mundus are strong, and we are the leaves to gather the sunlight.
Troll's blood, I'm glad you survived that! I am myself again. Drodda had us dancing to her witch's strings.nnYou're a hearty one, to best Lord Agomar! Who are you, exactly?

You ask so nicely, but no. Once you begin the game, only victory or defeat can set you free.nnYou, however, shall add an element of surprise and excitement to the game. Will you rush bravely into the fray? Or will you turn and run like a coward?
Yes, indeed. Everything is fine here at the Flagon. Plenty of mead, plenty of happy Nords!
I'm here from Firsthold to inspect the weapons. High Kinsman Rilis only wants the best armaments for the First Auridon Marines.
You looking for work? Good luck, friend. nnOnly job I could find. And I have to work with furballs and shorties. My mother would be so ashamed.
Hmm. Hate to see good mer like you lumped in with those damn cats. nnBut your people come here as cheap labor, same as the Khajiit. They should treat your kind better, I say.
Just got in from Silsailen, needed a new line of work. nnPay's lousy. And I have to work with furballs and shorties. But at least it's something.
Hey there, stranger. You here for work?
Enginaire's a good foreman, but she's Altmer. She doesn't know what it's like.
Zurka comes here all the way from Dune. She has very lucrative business, one of the best merchants in Elsweyr. nnAnd she can't get a single meeting with Condalin or Malanie!
The vault is open. Are you ready?
Sithis blind me! Look who it is! nnSeeing you is the first good news since we landed here. If you got in, maybe we can get out.
If you've talked to Pa, then I guess you got work to do.
Please, help them.
Did you find him?
Speak to this creature at your peril. I don't trust it, not a bit.nnIf it raises so much as a finger, I'll strike it down.
Go on, mate.nnIf things go well, I'll see you when this is all over.
Right behind you.
Well, you got it. Can we leave now?
A great prize you have claimed. I will not be sad to leave this place.
Ready when you are, friend.
Have you found the Thane's lair yet?
It must be here somewhere. Please, keep looking.
Hrmm. Well, belike you're right, when all's said and done. nnNow I'll just have to see what I can do for me new crew, here, with that old shaman's tricks.
I just got back from Narsis. Were you the one who saved the city?
We have no idea how much time has passed. I suspect our small village is long gone. The Hollow City will be our new home.

With Meridia's Lights, we can turn the tide of this campaign. Kireth said you came from the Hollow City. We shall go there once everyone has had a chance to rest.nnThank you for your help. You know, you remind me of one of my students.
Thank the Eight you found him. Thrice-blessed are you, my savior.
We never should have left Cloudrest. My mother was right.
We're lucky the Marines responded so quickly. Aetherius can wait, if you ask me.
This is unacceptable! And all my husband's fault!
Thank you for getting me out of there. I saw the flames from the road. I could have been trapped in my own home.
I hope you find her.
Please, you must help me! The Daedra tore my spirit free and ravaged my mind. I  I cannot remember the spell to drop the barrier!
I feel  strange. Like I've been asleep for a very long time.
My poor, sweet boy.
My head feels less foggy. I may try writing a song or two again.

Place the seeds on the bodies of the dead. Angof said that would help me. Keep me safe.nnWhen they force you to make a choice in all thisand they will make you chooseI wouldn't mind an ally who doesn't, you know, want to stab me.
Whatever that rune does, this one wants no part of it.nnMaybe you can figure out how to use it to our advantage. Might even provide an edge against the Observer.
Another hour and I drink free for the rest of the night!
You're back I see, with the pieces I need. I hope the guests weren't too much pests.nnBut please, Lady Estre wants to speak. Perhaps she'll provide the aid you seek!
I'm a little disoriented. But  did my sister just hit me?

If you manage to kill the champions of both Estre and Thallik, I'm not sure what happens next. No one has ever gotten that far.nnJust stay alive and remain wary. Who knows how the Observer will alter the playing field if you get too close to victory.
It will be so nice to rest. Finally, rest.
I just wanted to say  what I mean is .nnOh, bother! I'm not really very good at this. Thank you. For rescuing us, I mean. Thank you so much.
Help me. Before it's too late.
Once you use the death rune, get on with the killing. The transformation doesn't last very long.nnIf the power fades, just use the rune again.
You picked Estre to help?nnI  I think that's a good idea. She suggested we throw a party when I showed up. I guess it's a little more getting to work for you.
Remember. When the Observer asks for your decision, choose me!
Start by looking for Marq's special brew. If any is left, the smell might make him slightly less crazy.
I hope I never see another bandit again. Horrible people.
Defeat the champion of the warriors and convince An-Jeen-Sakka of the worthiness of your decision.
You may think you are clever, but your actions will come to naught.
Seems you know your way around a battlefield, friend. We could win the war tomorrow if we had a dozen the likes of you.nnCan I assume you took the rutter off their hands?
My beach! Mine! Get out of here! nnBet you're with those two crazy people. It's not yours. It's mine!

I have long dreamed of kind words and a way out, but I think this task is beyond you, my friend.nnThe first phylactery is up ahead, watched by impossible creatures. You cannot defeat them. No one can.
I'm not going anywhere until you find Mister Nurin. I know he's still alive.
Still no sign of William at the farm? I'm sorry to hear that.
Thanks for getting me out of there!
I'm going to have nightmares about this day. Damn the Daedra.
It's a good thing I was out hunting. I was able to warn my family in time.
Kill them. Kill the Dremora and stop the summoning!
What is your decision?
<<1>>! And she's unhurt! The Hist guided you, as I knew it would.nnBut did it also guide you to my ruby? Please, tell me!
You're lying! My father never would have done this.

I  I thank you. I didn't  I wasn't expecting you would be so capable. You've ended Anconath's torture, and freed a fragment of my soul.nnAre you willing to do more? My soul remains bound, and the Daedra are torturing others.
If you're lucky, you won't die before the amulet starts working, if it ever does.
Is the amulet charged? Did it work?
Well done. Very well done!

A powerful lich guards the last fragment, plucked out of history and summoned by my husband. He's ravaging the soul of one of my students.nnI would die again to help that studentbut I can't. Please, save him if you can.

I wish Nelhilda would forgive me, but I understand her anger. She has her soul back and her place in Sovngarde is assured. I can hold onto that, and I'll make sure that anyone else who comes here receives whatever aid I can provide.
I never hoped that I would ever be free, but I thank you for unbinding this fragment of my soul.nnYou've helped Faindor, too, and that brings me a sense of peace that I am unable to express.
You have freed not only my soul, but the souls of all the students caught in my husband's attack.nnYour actions right a wrong that was long overdue.
Don't worry, the Serpent is dormant for now.

<<1>> is under pirate attack! Worse, they climbed in through our portholes and breached the hull.nnI'll use their blood to swab the decks. Think they'll put more holes in my hull, do they? We had just finished repairs on the last ones!
Greetings, my friend. You did it. The undead fell in their tracks.nnThe pirates, they surrendered or fled. A good day.
At least we know what's going on at the lighthouse now.nnIt may take a while, but we'll send men down there as soon as we can spare them.

I suppose <<1>>'s death was just, but so many of my people were sickened because of what? An old feud between brothers? This is why you'll never see an Orc wear the Amulet of Kings.nnBut the bandits stopped their attacks, so you have my thanks.
Ha! I knew you'd done it the moment those undead fell to tatters!nnHalf of the pirates surrendered on the spot. They must've thought whatever you did to the undead would happen to them next!
Look, see? That abandoned boat is my only chance!nnPlease, give me my things. I need to get away from here!
I suppose you fancy yourself a hero.
The Amulet awaits. Take it so we can escape this place.
What have you learned? Whose tales are false?
You decided to help those  those  monsters? Instead of my people?nnI'm so mad I can't even talk to you right now!
This place  it does strange things to your mind.
Ozor, Salach, and Lidenar are free and Captain Angarthal is dead. I believe this day is getting better.nnI may have lost my ship, but you've restored my hope.
I told you I could get out on my own. Thank you for rescuing my employees. Can you make certain <<1>> knows?nnI think she was headed back toward Haven.

My contact is no wilting flower. You'll find him on the beach, I'm certain of it.nnLook, collect the payment yourself for all your trouble. As long as he doesn't leave without the mixture, we'll still have our side business. That's fair, yes?
Let's get out of here before my axe breaks.
Don't worry, I'll seal the portal behind us.
Greetings, Orc.
Well, I'd best get back to the Prowler. I expect the <<1>> will want all hands on deck.nnNeedn't bother her with this business, right? Right, right.
You can pass the "receive a quest" case now, if you haven't already.  Did you check your Quest Journal, map pins, and Tracker?
What do you say, outlander? Do you still stand with <<1>> Stronghold?
There are  more of you. Were you successful? You found allies?
You wouldn't know anything about proto-Ayleid literature, would you? I can't be certain if the references in these books are metaphors, or descriptions of actual events.nnNo matter, I'll work it out.
Go and find the stolen weapons. Return them to me and prove you're worth the Steel Mask's time.
I'm so hungry.
Just go about your business quickly, stranger.
You did it! Your little racer won the show.
Oh! You're back. So you weren't eaten by lions, then. Good!nnDid you have any luck with the journals?
Good luck with your froggy! Isn't frog racing the best?
Hhmph. Good luck. You'll need it with that creature.
You're lucky Bloodthirster is not competing. Your pathetic beast would not survive!
Did you find everything?
Did you do as you promised? Do my children know peace?
Your Dunmer blood proved true. Vox is defeated, order is restored. Well done.
So, how did it go?
You can pass the "receive a quest" case now, if you haven't already.  Did you check your Quest Journal, map pins, and Tracker?
What do you want? I've got to repair these things while I can.
This is not the time to talk. There are trolls in here!
The stronghold survived because of your help. We won't forget this.
Rumor has it you have the Red Rooks on the run. I'll sleep easier when the bandits have left town.
<<1>> won't be back. Knows if he shows his face in Stormhold, he'll get it smacked. Price of starting false rumors, right?
You know, this wine isn't half bad. And this cellar is nice and quiet. Cozy. Comfortable, even.nnI think I'm going to live down here forever.
Terrible business down in the ruins, eh?nnOoh, I should add it to my report!
Those Red Rooks may be gone, but I still don't think I want to do any work.
So many fleshlings running through the halls. Such obstreperous creatures!nnYou seem a fine specimen. I don't think I have one of your kind in my garden.
Rocks. Rocks with eyes. I went to get a closer look, and then she .nnWhy can't I remember?
Acquiring a Daedra's eyeball is a disgusting request, but it will release the binding, I'm certain of it.nnAnd if it doesn't, there should be some clean rags at our camp.
Guard duty is tougher than I thought. But I can't let <<1>> down.
Brute-vitar sealed us out. <<1>>'s fellows all dead, killed by dirty snake-ladies. No doubt this Pact-soldier kills poor <<1>> now.nnThis swamp, I hate it. Endless woe! Poor <<1>>!
Find Sergeant Stegine. He's up the road, in Dreughside.nnSo many dead.
No luck finding our valuables yet? Those Thorns need to be taught a lesson.
If you're looking for the Hall Steward, she's inside.
There's nothing as miserable as wearing heavy armor in the desert heat.nnI was born and raised here, but that doesn't make it anymore a comfort.
You heard the Guildmaster. nnSees-All-Colors. She murdered Jofnir.
Welcome to our little circle. I think you'll fit right in. nnYou can call me Milady. For now.

These ritual altars remain foreign to me. Dracien believes the Canonreeve is preparing a Worm Cult rite. Some sort of necromancy.nnIf this is true, Tamriel is in great danger. One Canonreeve with loyalties to the Worm Cult could mean others.

Look at this hovel. It's like the cavern itself is rotting. And the smell! I can taste it with every breath.nnThe Canonreeve must be dabbling in necromancy. She may even be Worm Cult. That would be fantastic.
I'd thank you, but I'm pretty sure you had your own reasons for helping me.
The more you struggle, the quicker the end comes. Had your fill yet?
Looks like we won't be putting into <<1>> anytime soon. I don't know how we're going to keep our schedule.
I'm glad to see the Reliquary restored. I suppose I need to find the jar of polish.
Mauloch's teeth, I can't believe Hareld is keeping us away from the docks. nnI thought when I joined the Fighters Guild I'd actually, you know, fight.
Wooden walls aren't going to help against what's in that mine!
Is that ? Xuth! You found my bow.
We'll make sure the Red Rooks know they aren't welcome in Crosswych. I think a dagger in the ribs sends that message loud and clear!
I think Tamien Sellan has the right idea. We need to fight back and show these Red Rooks that they can't just march in and take over our town.
You did it! Our way is clear!
Healer Dalen sent word that he arrived at Eidolon's Hollow safely. I'm so relieved.
Is the procession safe?
Have you found my family's remains.
I've reassembled the spider, but I must be able to control it.nnThat reminds medid you find the crystals?
It may not be much, but <<1>> scraped together a reward. We can't exactly pay you in catapults. Not if we want the Dominion to take us in.nnWhat you did for us  we won't forget it.
I await news of your success. Howls of dismay from across the river would be nice.
Ah, you've returned. Do you have the second book?
You're on the right path, Adept. Collect the essence we need to unlock this ancient structure.
I've been sent to ask for your help!
Ah, you're here. As punctual as a thespian. Very good.
We'll take charge from here. With any luck, we can relocate Koth and his tribe somewhere that they don't cause any more trouble. If not, well .nnGoblins should remember their place.
<<1>> said he wanted to speak with you. I'm sure he told me what it was about. Did he tell you?nnNo, that's  oh yeah  of course he didn't. He's around here somewhere, but I've forgotten where.
Ahh, it was so good to see their smiling faces. Hear their laughter. Thank you, dearie. Thank you from the bottom of Baan Dar's heart.
I hear they decided to let the Redguard envoy in to speak with the Duke.nnI guess there's a chance this thing won't turn into a full-blown battle.
Sir Hughes decided to let that redguard envoy in to speak with the Duke, and the soldiers went back to their camp.nnSo things are quiet here for now.
Too many elves! One will kill Byz, he knows it!
Shazah will be able to tell you all you need to know. Watch your steps, traveler.
Ah, there you are. I want to thank you for getting this book and cypher.
Khajiit very busy. Please do not get in our way.
Watch yourself here.
What a pity. The fun is over so soon.
I can't believe I forgot to announce you to the Duke. nnI really am sorry. I hope you can forgive me.
Byz say you want talk. Talk.
What did Shazah say? Are we going somewhere?
That was neatly done, the way you got Iriana and Shamal back.
Thanks again for your help. I think I'll stay here and get some strong drink in my belly before braving the roads again.
You've the scent of blood on you. Is the deed done?
No sign of my father yet?
It's you again, isn't it? Do you have the skulls?nnBlast, am I talking to a corpse again?
This one is certain the clergy will confirm what we suspect. To think, a Moon Hallowed in our midst!
Research never goes as one expects.
Those raiders are still out there. You're getting cold feet? Typical.

I was so happy to see Sir Hughes escape from whatever darkness held him in thrall, but it seems now, his fate is more unclear than ever. nnWhatever he may have done, I would counsel the duke to show mercy. Always mercy.
Just seeing my father's old sword fills me with courage! I can do this, I think!
Such horrific power. My people were helpless before it.
These ruins hold knowledge that has been lost for millennia. Perhaps when this crisis is over.
This is no place for the living. Begone!
Living and yet without a soul. How can this be?
Violation! The living desecrate our sanctuary. Death to all!
Before we go, there is something you should know.
The Three must have sent the Maulborn to help us. They're so kind and generous.
I can't be sick. I refuse to be sick. Peasants get sick, not nobles!
This warm, awful land! The heat breeds disease like a venison carcass draws flies.
I was so moved by the Maulborn proclamations that I came all this way to join their movement. But they refused my offer to help.
I'm not so sure about this. Some of the Maulborn seem all right, but most of them rub me the wrong way.
Is Yngrel dead? I can see from your face he isn't. Please kill him soon.
Death is a necessary part of life. But some deaths are more necessary than others.
I don't know how to thank you. I don't know what my girls would do without me.
Hello there, stranger. Got something for me?
I can't watch.
What? Are you expecting someone to knit a sweater while we wait for you?nnNo one is going to do that! Do I look like I knit?
The Hound is my concern, and mine alone. Yet, I just can't leave the Silvenar in danger.nnWhen will he leave me be?
Let's take the fight to these rabble.
That  that was terrifying! I was afraid I'd be stuck in that body forever! Curse you!
That worked perfectly! I can't believe it!
That was quick. Don't tell me something went wrong.
Just clear the way for my messenger in case someone sends reinforcements  or attacks the Dominion elsewhere.nnWe'll take back Velyn Harbor, one district at a time.
Hear me out. I've no wish to battle you today.
You not allowed in. Go 'way.
Khajiit has been waiting. You have the weapons?
The Sea Drakes will fall apart without Helane. They'll be at each other's throats in a day.
I've said everything I'm going to say about the attack on Velyn Harbor. I'm certain my superiors will see the wisdom in my actions.
Good to see you again. Redguard invaders in Velyn Harbor doesn't surprise me. But the Drublog clan? They side with the Bosmer in times of war.nnWe need to find out what's changed.
Speak to my father. He made the trap for <<c:1>>, so he can break it.nnHe's at home in the lower arena. I hope he speaks to you.
Off with you. I am too busy to entertain visitors.
Well, well, well. See that? That's an impressive trap door for a simple farmhouse cellar. nnI love it when my hunches pan out!
Quit staring at me. Leave me be or kill me, just get it over with!
Key's probably on him. Go ahead and grab it.nnUgh, he smells like rotten grapes. I'm going to get cleaned up. I'll meet you at the farm.
If you can help <<c:1>> again, we'd all be in your debt.
That was a good fight.
Perhaps we shall fight soon.
You need to fight the rest before you fight the best. Me, being the best.
Beat the brawlers and then I'll see what you're made of.
I've done all I can, but the king seems to slip further away every hour. nnI'm afraid there is no way to enter the dream either. There's something different this timesomething far more dangerous.
Prove yourself against some brawlers. Perhaps then we can test each other.
I hope you've been busy, friend. My heist is all planned and I'm itching to go.
After you've kicked around the pups, come back here. I'll bite your head off.
What brings you to this trashpit?
That cat is going to get an earful when I find him.
Business should pick up as soon as the Mabrigash get used to our presence.
Who are you? What're you doing here?
Go muck around with the chumps.
Please hurry. Preserving this collection has been my life's work.
Another torturer from Helane, even uglier than the last one.
I pledge my life to helping King Emeric  and to destroying anything, anyone, associated with Vaermina.
Don't know who you are, but you better run if you don't want the Sea Drakes to gut you.
Are you all done?
This bucket is AWESOME.
Who in Oblivion are you?
Get me out of here and I'll owe you.
Disrupt the rituals, kill the cultists. Drain the energy from their defilements.
I sense great power in the staff. You've done well.
What's in those portals, anyway? Never mind. I don't want to know.
I'm going to wait right here. I've got an unnatural aversion to alits and I'm not afraid to admit it. Just let me know when you've found that hidden door.
Go get 'em! I'll leave uniforms around for you once I get my knives into a few more cultists.
I can't face <<1>> without our goods.
Are you ready to head inside?
Welcome back to Wayrest, my friend. Your presence is reassuring in these troubles times.nnDo you have news regarding the Dream Shard?
I recognize you from the stories. You're the one who helped save Count At-Tura, aren't you? He's  an old friend.nnI'm glad to make your acquaintance. Don't mind the guillotine. It's just for show.
As soon as I can travel, I'm heading back to the Telvanni coast.
The Drublog will show no mercy. Please, get into the Mages Guild and the Trade Hall quickly.nnIf the townsfolk are still alive, you'll find them there.
Why are you still here?
Home at last. I can't thank you enough for saving us!
Oh, it's you. Did you expect me to gush with praise, hmm?nnToo bad. I should've stayed in the tree stump .
Feluz has been a little grumpy without his moon-sugar candy, but it's for the best.nnAs soon as there's space in the town square, we'll open a shop. Again, thank you.
Rama, dead. I can't believe it. I'm going to miss the old scoundrel.
Leave me alone. I have to earn my keep around here just like any other person. Malanie doesn't pay me meager wages to lolligag.

This was my first real trial of a full strength potion. I gathered a small horde of thunderbugs, but the elemental energy was too much. The ensuing explosion threw me into the river. nnAs you can see, my contingency plan was successful.
Get in there and show them what you're made of.
One less Ayleid Relic to plague our world. Good!
Now for the heist I mentioned earlier .
Can't wait to get this heist over and be off this rock.
Do be careful where you store that rod. The trigger is sensitive. Were it to discharge prematurely, the results could be dramatic.
Traitor! Out of my sight! How could you keep that thing?
How wonderful. A tourist.
Don't worry about changing in front of me. I won't peek.
Onsi's bones, what is it now?
Oh, I could lounge out here forever. So nice.
You're in my light.
You return with treasures and a ghost. You have been busy.

You'll find the graveyard near the Daggerfall cathedral. I shall meet you there.nnAnd know this. My master believes you will make the right decision. That's the only reason we're helping you. If you make the wrong decision, it shall cost you dearly.
Ah, my lowly servant! You're just in time.
Like a rat. On fire.
My friend! Welcome back. Do you have some good news?
I can't catch them! They're too big for me!
Have you seen Captain Kaleen? She's supposed to deliver some papers and I'm getting very impatient.
The city's defenses are turned against the Silvenar! This shouldn't be possible.
When my crew turned traitor, I never thought I'd see Betnikh again. Feels good.
Who are you? You weren't on the excavation team.
Make sure Kalari knows I'm thinking about her, all right? Warms an old man's heart to know a pretty girl thinks well of him.
Go  go now!
Honestly, I don't think I'll ever get used to the way he pops around. But at least he's back in one piece and not complainingfor now.
Go  go now!
Damned Colovians. They pick the most inconvenient times to get brave.nnSoldier? Report.
I love a good sneak attack. The look in a man's eye when the knife goes in. Ooh! I just got chills.
I'd shake your hand, but it's covered in steaming shalk guts. But by Baan Dar, why not? Put her there!

Now that the Covenant has that artifact, the Aldmeri Dominion won't dare attack!nnYou're a hero. Don't let anyone tell you different. My brothers, and all of the High King's soldiers, owe you their lives.
That poor man. Killed in the street and no one even knows who was responsible?nnI think I might pack my things and go visit my cousin in Alcaire.
The Lyris I knew loved life and all it had to offer. Sober and boring is no life for a hot-blooded warrior woman!
Don't let him influence her. It took her years to overcome her drinking problem. If she starts again, she may never stop!
You were right to destroy that cursed relic. I honor Kaleen, but she has lost her way.nnNo one should have that power. Certainly not Fahara'jad.
No. I didn't see the murderer. I'm just one woman. I can't see everything all the time.nnOne more person accuses me of neglecting my duty and they're going to get a gauntlet to the face.
A friendly face! Great day for an invasion, isn't it?
The crew of the Spearhead grows again. I did not think to see it so soon. The sun shines on us.
I'm innocent. The Headman framed me, I swear it!
You return. What did you learn of the Bloodthorn plans?
Enjoy your cut, partner. Don't spend it all in one place. As I, no doubt, will.
I will carry the ring with faith to Rawl'kha. The priests there will know just where to tend to it. Thank you again.
I have nothing to say to you.
Kalari will be all right, you will see. Just needs some time to deal with what has happened.nnGo, speak to Ezzag.
That was a great job, Baan Dar is very pleased with you!
I should've never let <<1>> leave my side!
If you ever get your hands on more of those fantastic Nord garments, I'd be happy to buy them from you.
That Nord book you gave me was very  colorful. I may have to read it again.
I am once again a man worthy of the blood of my ancestors!nnLet's have that shield, then.
Amazing to think he gave his life to destroy that thing. Don't worry about us here. With the vault out of the picture, the Colovians will pull back before long. Good work, soldier.
The sooner you can re-light that tower, the better. People here get nervous whenever it goes out.
I believe Mephala's reaction was proof: the temple is sealed. Well done there, I suppose.
Ahh, traveler. Fivefold venerations upon you. I recognize you from Telenger's description. What brings you to the Falinesti Autumn site?
Welcome to the Falinesti Autumn site, traveler. I'm with the team Telenger has brought. You're just as he described you. What brings you this way?
Welcome to the Falinesti Autumn site. Ghadar is surprised, you are just as Telenger described you. This one is working with the great mage to study the site.
Are you well? That was quite the show.
We'll rebuild the collection. You've done the Society, and by association, all of Tamriel, a great favor.
Less wounded than usual. I'd say we definitely have the ogres on the run now.
Hey, is that the Goblin king's crown? You killed him?
Damn that Angof! One death was not enough for that bastard! Look at the trouble he continues to cause me!
