This will be remembered as the fight that turned the tide! nnThe General will have moved up to establish a new base at the tower! You go on up.
Thank you.
It is out of my hands now, my friend. It has been an honor serving with you.
There is tension in the air. Can you smell it? Subtle, poisonous. Exciting.
Go, go. Kalari should not have to deal with her father's legacy alone.
We've got a deal.
The little rat is all yours. I'm going to drink even more heavily now.
<<1>>'s been gone for hours. I don't know what I'll do if  if he doesn't come back.
Without that sap, <<1>> might not see another year. Gods willing, this plant'll be his salvation!
<This Redguard died recently. Something is clutched tightly in his hand.>
You've slaughtered Zurana's men. And now you come looking for her blood, yes? nnPerhaps there is another way.
What are you still doing here?! Go find Bob!
Keep moving. I'm in no mood to chat.
Ah I see you have returned. Did you find anything?
I only hope Shagol hasn't lost my best axe forever. This one cannot seem to keep its edge.
You're back! Found anyone else to help us with this heist?
There's three folks Captain Kaleen wants to help with her heistCrafty Lerisa, Jakarn, and Neramo. She told me about 'em. Who do you want to know about?
Get out of here. We're done.
Off you go. The corn should take just seconds to gather. I'm far too busy thinking to do it myself.
Go on about your business. There's nothing to see here.
Be careful in there! There're things in the shadows.
Another victim of the forest? Or have you been spared its horrors?
I'm thankful that you came along. I would have spent my entire life waiting and wondering what became of my husband.
My cousin never returned from the mines. I'm worried sick.nnHe's a miner at Bearclaw Mine. Are you coming from there? I hope he's all right.
You've betrayed me and the Covenant with your actions. I can't stand to be in your company anymore. You'll leave here without me.
As long we have breath in our lungs, we'll keep the Autumn site healthy and growing.
This one overheard. He is called Razum-dar, and on behalf of Queen Ayrenn, he thanks you.
Keep as quiet as you can.nnSignal me if you see any suspicious corpses. My arrows will make short work of them.
Start in Grimfield. Warchief Tazgol sent a few scouts to harry the Bloodthorn there until we can deal with them. We need to stop them from raising more zombies.
I knew you couldn't be trusted. What do you think King Emeric will do with that cursed artifact? You should have destroyed it.
Without that plant sap <<1>> might as well be dead.
Thank tha gods those Colovians are gone now. They wree disturbing my peave something fierce. And I had an anniversary to celebrate, damnit it!

So the true culprit behind Lakana's murder was indeed Vaermina? I'm glad to know her plot against my brother was ultimately thwarted.nnI'm glad we spared Sir Hughes as well. I understand he's doing penance at Pariah Abbey.
Though this battle is important, Aiden Direnni expects my blade to lead the assault against a key Alessian camp to the north. nnAnd what a glorious battle it will be! I'll be leaving shortly.
I heard a lovely, agonized shriek from Zich. Is it dead?
I can smell the sugar leaf on you. Did you get three leaves?
Yes, yes. Let's get this over with.
At last! <<1>> is defeated! The tortured souls, now avenged! nnLong have I waited for this day!
Ahh, such a lovely warmth against the temple stones. So good to smell pumping blood in these halls again.
What is it, Visanne?
Zal-sa is done. You can tell <<1>> that he has quit. nn<<2>> may be able to deal with all this work. Zal-sa cannot!
I have nothing else to say to you.
Bandit. Butcher. I am not afraid of you.
We have nothing else to discuss. You will determine your own fate.
Stay your blade, orc. The fight is over.
Well, what are you waiting for? Put on the disguise and let's get a look at you!
Ah! You are the five-clawed walker who helped at <<1>>, yes?nnYour story will buy <<2>> sugar in every city between here and Dune, so thank you!

Don't mind me. I'm just trying to compose something for the Duke and his lady. I understand she has taste and pays good coin.nnThat's if they stay together long enough for me to perform. There's a lot of tension in that court right now.
How many innocent people have died in those mines? The Red Rooks must pay.
Seems like the campaign against the ogres never ends!nnI heard they're still close to Wayrest.
Have you seen the guillotone in the marketplace? I think they're going to do something about that Dreamer cult.nnI'll be glad when this is all over.
This bodes well. With the beach clear we can take the fight to our enemy.
Enter Warcaller Targoth's memories. Witness my fate.
The storms on this island are not natural, and I fear that they play a part in the Maormer plan to attack Malabal Tor.nnFind their source and silence them.
Everyone's heard what you did at Firebrand Keep. I'll tell you now, it was a mistake letting that man live, after what he did to the Duchess.
If you have come to help, tend to the wounded first. They may turn if left to die.
And so, it begins. The remainder of the story has yet to be written. It is your story, now.
You have saved the Claw from true darkness. It is your sacred charge, now.
Agh  that hurt. Probably should not have done that, but  you have to find him. Fort Grimwatch is in the Northern Woods, high up the Reaper's March. This one thinks  that is where he's gone.
You arrived at an auspicious time in Crosswych. I came here to examine the citizens for signs of lycanthropy and found the town overrun by bandits.
I won't tell you anything. I won't!
When I get my hands on that useless Shagol, I'll rip his skin off!
I'm going to catch my breath before I head back.nnIt sure feels good to have feeling back in my arms and legs again.
There you are. I worried you met your end in the ruins. The souls of the dead still walk, and yet their torment has lessened. What did you do?
I'm still waiting.
You proved yourself capable in Bthzark. I trust you can handle whatever this ruin holds. I will remain at a safe distance.
What kind of game are you and my brother playing? No, don't tell me. Just  be careful.
Fine with me if the Pact controls Brindle. I just don't like them all over my town.
I can't believe this is happening. I think you should put a stop to it.

If you see any soldiers in need, help them out. Any one who falls  the Heritance will just raise them to fight against us.nnBut the most important thing is getting to the Mane though. He dies here, that's one more blow to the Dominion.
Akkhuz-ri was right. With Indaenir's talents and your skills, you make a powerful force for goodness.nnThough Naemon remains at large, this one believes the tide has already turned.
I know what to do, but you'll need to get me close to those rifts.
I could hear the fighting from here! Either you won or your armor's really well made. Now go lift that embargo, the ship doesn't feed herself!
Go ahead. Do whatever you have to do. I won't hold it against you. nnI've killed a man or two myself who owed me money. It's just the way it goes.
Well done, by Mauloch!  It'll take them weeks to find all of their bruises.
I'll be better next time we meet.
You're strong, I'll give you that.
I'm not sure I want to make a career out of crafting mead, but I sure enjoy drinking the stuff! Come to think of it, I could use a mead right about now.

These orders make it sound like the Stormfists want something from inside the royal crypts. nnAnd they were actually signed by Fildgor Orcthane! That means the Skald-King's traitorous brother has returned.

Any questions you have about the job or your compensation should be directed to my father at the main camp to the north east.nnNow if you don't mind, I want to enjoy the nature all around us. Time to do more fishing!
If bigots like Talmo had their way, we would all be speaking Altmer.

Before I return this journal to Guifford, I must try to find a way to stop Faolchu. His werewolves can't be allowed to continue their attacks. My brother barely survived his encounter with the creatures.
The end of your journey is in sight, Moon Hallowed. Take the last few steps.
I heard what you said! You told that filthy lizard about our deal! Well, there's no going back now! Give him the ingredients and I'll pay the price.nnFancy me trusting some strange wanderer
The Colovians will never see me. Field craft is my passion, you know?
I hope the Divines will still listen. For At'avar.
Thank you for showing those stubborn fools we mean business.
Juluda feels so alive! Hah! Bring on more of those Colovian bastards!

So, you've decided to help that drunkard, have you? No, no, do not deny it  your perfitudiousness is as plain as the flagrebex on your wheezax.nnGo, give her the meats you hunted. I know the truth, but can't prove it. She wins.
So weak, but still alive. My father. Where is he?
You've saved my career and my life, friend.nnWithout my instrument, I'm worthless as a bard. My singing voice sends mudcrabs scurrying away.
Are you prepared to hear my riddle?
I heard you helped my friends in Crosswych. You have my thanks for that.
It was a tough choice, but you made the right one. Good job, my friend.
All that trouble for a hunk of red rock. I hope this is all worth it.
I'm satisfied that fools won't be allowed to tinker with the relic, but I regret the lost opportunity to study it.
Give the husk to Rhea. She needs it for . I'm sure she'll explain it.
You made the right choice. I wonder if we'll get paid?
All clear
Thanks for keeping the relic. You probably saved my brothers' lives!
Your choice was the right one. Do not dwell on it.
We have to focus on retaking Camlorn. It's all we have time for right now.
Marius cares only for himself. When I was dragging you out of that poison he did nothing. In fact, he mocked me!
<<1>> was a great man. He is with Arkay now, watching over us.
Yay
We  we have been betrayed.
We need you back at the fortress. Right now!
I hope you find the supplies we need. Lives depend on it.
May you learn much from these visions.
I  Hallowed, you must know. I would never turn on the Queen that way. These visions Hunal speaks of, they  they could never come to pass in the light of day.
Ho there adventurer! We need all the strong arms we can get, care to join us?
I need time to think. Becoming a bandit and exploring the world was all my brother and I thought about as kids. Now? I just don't know. I hope he's okay still.
So I guess if Sir Hughes killed the duchess then, crazy or not, the duke is going to want him to answer for that.nnI guess this means we're going to have to find a new leader .
<<1>> was worried for a moment, but we've done it. The <<2>> is ours!
Kindly traveler, thank you. I thought I'd never see another friendly face again.
You should have listened to Jakarn. That relic should have been destroyed.
Giving Irien the slip wasn't easy. He said he would be right over.nnI wonder if she caught him? I'd pay to see that argument.
While I respect your heroism at Carzog's Demise, I cannot endorse your decision to keep that terrible relic. For once, Jakarn and I agree on something.
How could you give that artifact to humans? Get out of my sight.
I assume my family wasn't especially pleased with an outsider prying into our affairs. nnRemember, it was your idea.
You must be ready to leave this place, traveler.
You have done the work of the Moons and the Green both, my new friend. Our people will remember you for this kindness.
You made the right decision. Our homeland is safer with that artifact than without it.
I swore never to sail with you again. But <<1>> has asked me to sail you to Glenumbra, which I will do.
<This Colovian soldier has stopped breathing.>
Was destroying that artifact really the right thing to do? The captain doesn't think so. Still, I'm glad I didn't have to make that decision.
Hey, I heard about what you did at that ruin. Good for you. With that artifact, the Daggerfall Covenant will be stronger than ever.
I wish you clear night skies on your travels, Hallowed.
Get down! Dremora are just up the path.
The Moons send me nothing but woe.
target: Le Lune non mi mandano altro che calamit.

source: We owe you so much. Finally, the Aldmeri Dominion can truly be called an alliance.nnBut, I'm afraid there's no rest for the heroic. I have a message for you.
Never trust an outsider! When Lokra dies in some ancient ruin, you will be to blame. Get out of my sight.
First the Whisperer. Now vampires. You think we'd learn to stay out.
<The Argonian lies unconscious on the ground. A poisoned arrow remains in a fresh wound. It should be removed.>
Come on back after you talk to Sir Lanis.nnYou know, if you feel like it.
Our thoughts are with you, Hallowed. May the Green watch over you.
May the end of your Path be marked by no sorrows, no sadnesses.
I don't claim the Bright Moons listen to me, Hallowed  but you are in my prayers.
Time to prepare for the Two Moons Path. Travel well with the Moon-Hallowed, my friend.
I smell blood! And do I hear the clacking of senche fangs? You've completed my bounty, haven't you?
Don't worry  don't worry about me.
I don't trust the Pact one bit. Dunmer have always been the black sheep of Elves.
I took the liberty of weaving you into the ward so you can find the grove again.
Apologies for making you travel, but Zadala is already late for her meeting. This one serves the Queen. As you do.
Quiet now, or you'll scare all the fish away.
So many names. So many faces. Such terrible understanding.
The ritual is complete, and the Daedra of Ilmyris guard their very prison. Orthenir is caretaker now, until another comes to take his place.
It is always Hazazi who gets the worst jobs.
Raz looks good in this form. But then, Raz always looks good. Queen Ayrenn could maybe learn a thing or two from this one.
Are you looking to talk to me? You have that look about you.
When you're ready to go, just tell the cat  the queen, I mean. nnLike I said, may Baan Dar be with you. I hope you two can pull this off.
Hissmir isn't far. It should be easy to spot, since it contains some of our larger xanmeers. Pyramids, left by the ancients.

My scouts came back singing your praises! They said the Wood Orcs broke quickly after you killed Chieftain Thragdosh and unleashed the guardians.nnHmph. I wasn't exactly expecting you to succeed. Seems there's more to you than meets the eye.
I'm keeping watch outside, just in case any of the Exile's remaining forces try to cut us off.nnI heard you sowed chaos in there, and the army was able to just sweep in. I wish I could have seen it.
A friendly face? Does this mean the Daedra haven't killed everyone?
At last, someone who isn't trying to kill me.
Are you the Moon Hallowed?
I felt Fildgor's life expire. It left ripples throughout this realm. You killed him, didn't you?
We all ask ourselves what our purpose is in life, yes? So nice to know yours. So nice to know you are needed.
Can't feel my tail.
What are you?
As soon as the trolls wander off, we can get the loggers back to work. With the new roads being built and the King's work camp nearby, this place is worth a fortune!
I'm thankful that you came along. I thought for sure I'd never see my <<z:1>> again.
My cousin never returned and I'm worried sick.nnHe told me he was going to Icehammer's Vault. Did you come from there? Do you have news about my cousin?
Thank goodness you came by when you did. It would have been terrible to die before I got to see my sister's wedding.
No need to gloat
target: I saw it all. Clearly my hunters need more training.

source: Thank you, seafarer. nnIt is better if I remain here to supervise as best I can, but I know the king would want to be informed of what has befallen us as soon as possible.
Atarus is pretty dangerous, watch yourself.
The logging chief's cabin is at the other end of the camp. Just make sure you watch out for the trolls and the spriggans.
This should be good.

What madness. Soldiers died thinking our own ranks betrayed us. I'd like to feed those skin-stealers to a wamasu with the flux.nnI saw <<1>>'s guard lead him away before the attack. If his guard were skin-stealers, he's in grave danger.
Why don't you face a real warrior?
That was a surprise.
Impressive fighting.

Go find Thane Harvald at the camp. If he has any sense, he'll help us without involving that whiny Prince Irnskar. nnI'll deal with Guard Hloenor to make sure she doesn't spread word of this to anyone.
Go on. I must catch my breath, then I will meet you at the warehouse. nnThank you, seafarer, and may the gods be with you.
You should always address the king first when we're in the palace. That's not only the custom
I hear Lokra will be leaving on your ship. Good. She would never have been happy otherwise.
Lokra ignores the wishes of her clan. She fails all of us with her selfishness!nnBut I don't blame you. She chose to leave. That is her shame to bear.
Dremora and Shadowed Path cultists. How can we ever hope to defeat such foes?
Life is never certain. I take a torchbug, attach it to my hook, which ends its life, and hopefully, that of a fish as well.nnNothing's biting, though. Haven't been for days. It's a sign.
Need help with the trials or something? That's not what I do.nnThese xanmeers don't dig themselves out and keep clean of the muck. Neither do the other ruins.
I never thought I'd say this, but I think Lerisa has it wrong.nnBretons can't be trusted with an artifact of that power. You should have destroyed it.
Excuse me, but I'm meeting someone. Alone. Please be on your way.
I came here to get away from people. All their talk, talk, talk! Who cares which lizard killed which mer?nnI've got enough to worry about without listening to their noise.

There you go. Give the guards a kick and tell them to get to work. I've got cargo to unload.nnIf the guards can't help us, look for the dockmaster. Maybe he's got half a brain  unless the zombies have eaten it, of course.
My friend! I didn't think we would meet each other again so soon. I have great news.

Stop! You have no idea what you're doing. Those relics are the property of the Night Mother.nnWe felt their emanations the moment you removed them from their resting places, thief. Give them to me or pay the price.
target: Stop! You have no idea what you're doing. Those relics are the property della Madre Notte.nnWe felt their emanations the moment you removed them from their resting places, thief. Give them to me or pay the price.

source: Can it be? Are we really free of this place?

I think you made the right choice after all. The Shadowscales have battled our enemies for years  I should trust them.nnAnd I do. Their leader promised I'll be safe and I believe her. I hope to see you again, though. Take care.
The Bright Moons are with you, Hallowed. Shazah will be a credit to her name, leading her people with wisdom. And Khali's strength will be more than a match for the Dark Mane's savagery.
I can barely walk, much less fight.nnGo on without me. Find the others who survived. Our leader, Sud-HareemI'd bet anything he's still alive. Save him if you can.

I don't think I'd be much use to you in this condition. Go on, leave me here. There may be others who need your help.nnAnd if you find a Redguard named Sud-Hareem, tell him I'm here. Tell him I'm waiting for his orders.
Father! Sud-Hareem!nnMy father's somewhere nearby. I heard him calling to me. At least, I think I heard him  or was it the whispers?  Maybe they're affecting me after all.
We've sent the recruits out to help where they can. nnWe'll hold the hall. We will hold!

I sensed the darkness in the heart of the one you fought, but he has already been defeated, has he not? And those like him  they may not all share his darkness.nnYou should have me call these people enemies, though?
I'm going to miss old Ezreba. Damned shame.
Be careful. <<1>> is tougher than he looks. And he looks pretty tough.
We've escaped!
You found him! Sheggorath's Tongues, lad. These ones thought you dead! nnMuzag's family owes you many thanks, walker-friend. And Tand-ma owes you his life.
If you pass through Dune, please join us for a meal. This family will always call you friend.
You have returned my Tand to me! I don't know how I would have gone on without him. Your kindness will never be forgotten. How did you get him out of there?
Still alive I see! Always good news. Never know what might happen out there.nnAm stuidying with the monks. Learning their ways. Very fascinating. Should try it some time.
My lesser minions barely slowed you down. I'm impressed. But you're too late. I've already begun the ritual. Once it ends, my corruption will spread throughout Xal Ithix!
That was fast, but I'm not surprised! Did you find the things we need to build you a guardian?

So you commanded the general to turn around and fight on our behalf instead?nnI suppose it makes sense. If the villagers of Vullain remain trapped in the Shadow Wood, why should the general go free? Very well then.

Three of the binding stones are up ahead. Each Keeper defends a stone, so be prepared to face them.nnAnd be wary of Rilis. He will no doubt attempt to  speak with you. I will prepare for a direct battle with him and meet you at the fourth stone.
Such a close race! Unfortunately, your little bit of stewmeat did not win.
What  what was that? Thank you for saving me. Did Halindor send you?
I have barely set foot within these hallowed walls and I already feel a thousand times better!nnAnd now that you are here, we can determine our next move against the vile Molag Bal.
The Dominion has grown quiet.
Being a scout isn't really my ideal job. I would prefer to be guarding a lively market.

Thanks for rescuing my companions, even though it means I won't be able to sit down for a while. Skordo was so mad at me! He's got me out here keeping watch so I don't get into any more trouble.nnMe? I want to be in the tavern.

This city shall serve you well against Molag Bal. Know that every choice you make in Coldharbour will have an effect on the Hollow City.nnIt shall be reborn with every person you save, forged into a weapon by your own hands.
This one admires your efforts, but the match is not yours.
I want to punch Tharn in the throat with every fiber of my being, but I'll be civil. Just keep him out of my face.
Make it quick, that necromancer bastard could be back at any second!
Arkay preserve us, you're as battered and bruised as a peach in a sack of rocks! Bit of the old derring-do, was it?nnNo matter. You'll be needing an escape route, no doubt?
The Elder Scroll of Altadoon has been returned to its rightful place!
I knew it! There's no way she could have been the assassin. See for yourself!

<<1>> found ceremonial garb in the chest behind me. He made it past Dominion guards, but one of their tigers sniffed him out. His wounds weren't too severe.nnYou could use the garb to seek out <<2>>. Just keep an eye out for tigers.
I'll answer your questions. As long as they're not spy questions.
Ezreba will leave Greenhill, never to return.
Take her straight on up to Lord Tharn, he'll want to question her personally. Hazim can help direct you.
What is it? My husband has just returned home from the tavern. He is very hungry. nnIf I don't prepare his dinner quickly  well, I simply do not have time to chat right now.
<<1>> will be with our leader. Meet with them, or don't.
Head down hill. <<1>> will be there with our leader.
You did what you thought was best, of course.
Why does the Dominion send Hazazi to places like this?
When you need my warriors we shall be at your side!
I knew that Dremora was going to be interesting.
That troll was not worthy of your greatness. Perhaps you should choose another.
It's you again! The hunters say the mist has lost its sickly tint. Did you find the source?
I have promised to stay my blade for the present. Go on, hear his last words, meaningless as they are.
No more. Please. I'm not like them!
I will meet you at the exit.
<The statue holds the Gem of Endurance.>
I've got your back, good looking.
Fighting the undead always dulls the sword.
The guar watches carefully. What are the mighty wamasu's intentions?
<The statue holds the Gem of Endurance.>
<The statue holds the Gem of Endurance.>
Hurry, Targoth! Stop this magic!
Free me or kill me, Orc. Do not bore me with words.
Targoth! Our victory is near!
Trust me, the Black Daggers need to die. They're getting too powerful. No one's safe from them.
What are you waiting for? Stop King Renwic before he destroys us!
There is always more work to be done.
Thank you for your able council. May bright moons light your path.
Nice ship.
I'm glad we could help get the Prowler seaworthy. If the Sea Vipers are causing any more trouble, the Dominion needs all the ships it can get.
The gods brought us here for a reason. Damned if I know what it is.
Spotted some Sea Elves watching the ship. They don't look friendly.
Word reached the palace that Aldmeri forces were here, so the king sent me right away. nnLooked like many of the Elves were already dead. Where did they come from?
Make your purchase quickly, then go.
Warcaller. Does he live or die?
Can't you see that I'm busy here. Please leave me alone.
I'd suggest you leave, before.
Dark moons, traveler. She was just trying to keep her love alive!
You looking for more glory? Get going, like Ezreba.
Go away.
You're in my way.
My axe is very sharp.
Have you seen any fresh meat?
What is your will? Does the queen live or die?
It is your choice. Does the priest live or die?
We have the king's child. Does she live? Or die?
Please take care of those necromancers. It gives me the creeps thinking about what they're up to in that cave.
The water weakens <<1>>, but I can't hold him for long. Quickly, go to <<2>>. Tell him I did what must be done.
Go, quickly. I feel <<1>>'s weakness fade. Hurry, tell <<2>> of the plan's success.nnBut don't mourn for me, friend. I earned a useful fate. Few can say the same.
Bruma is east of here. Hafza's goods are expensive, but she's the best supplier I can find. I hope the bandits don't come back before I'm restocked.
Good to see you again, my friend! These sea rats came without warning!
Hey there friend. I have a secret, if you promise not to tell, I'll let you in on it.
Your marine friends helped with repairs and protected our sailors from a Sea Viper ambush. Don't know their thoughts on privateers, but I wouldn't turn them away if they decide to sign on.
You have no idea what it feels like to have a Khajiit scratching around inside your head.
The Horns of the Deep! They must be destroyed!
I hope we have time to resupply before leaving Glenumbra. They have a good selection here.
So this is where we part ways, good looking. I still think you made the wrong decision, but I think I'll actually miss you.
This is actually quite fun. Look at him squirm.
We've all agreed. He's going to choose one way or the other. Or we're throwing him off the boat!
The irony is delicious. You could cut it with a knife. Or anything else, for that matter.
Ha. Those ladies are such fools! Jakarn and I have already agreed.nnWe're going to run off together and have grand adventures!
Well, if it isn't the hero of Betnikh.
I want to go back to Stros M'Kai, but no one will sail me there. My life couldn't get worse.
I was so certain I wanted to sail with Captain Kaleen. But I still can't believe she was in favor of keeping that awful relic.nnI think I might take Lambur's offer and join her crew.
Ah, my friend from Betnikh. I see you are doing well. Have you heard the latest from Daggerfall?
Oh. Don't mind me. Just making sure these cabinets are secure.
I was wondering if we would see you again! I could hug you.
Well. That was an awful lot of drama, wasn't it? I think I'm about done here. It's time to sail on my own boat.nnStay safe. We'll meet again.
I never did get to thank you for saving us from Helane's pirates. Wherever you go, friend, I hope you stay safe.
I think my hand's starting to heal. One day, I'm going back to Stros M'kai to take my vengeance on those Sea Drakes.nnOnsi watch over you, my friend.
Lambur's starting her own crew. I'm going with her. Now I just need to tell Captain Lerisa.
Oh! Don't do that. Don't sneak up on me.nnWhat's this? What am I doing? I'm checking the manifests, of course. As if I would steal something.
Why have you come to Captain Kaleen's ship?

You made a decision. The specifics do not matter. We would not be here if not for you, and Betnikh would be in the hands of a cult.nnI do not know if I will sail with Kaleen or Lambur, but I would sail with you any time.
Thanks again. Not getting turned into a zombie is the second best thing to happen to me all day!

I hope the message will give her some solace  and perhaps soften her heart so she will not be so angry when I return.nnShe is in Sentinelpossibly in the inn. Tell her I found Sabasad's remains, and that I love her and I will soon be home.
Can you not see that I am reading? Can you not leave me to my book?nnPlease. This is all I have left.
You're from off the island, aren't you? I don't serve outsiders.
I don't have any more gold. Give me more time.
Skulreid is in Cropsford. It's a small farm town southwest of Drakelowe Keep. He always pays a good coin for my fertilizer.
I hope the Pact can be trusted to leave Cropsford, and Zenithar's shrine, unmolested.
Yes, strike down the old Elf. His apprentice isn't my size, but she has possibilities.
Wayfarer, you try my patience. Either tell me something of importance or be on your way. Wait. Is that what I think it is? That belongs to my family.
Welcome to the Wayrest Mages Guild Hall. Do I detect some interest in membership?
Who are you? What do you want?
I never expected to see Covenant soldiers in Cropsford. Not sure how I feel about that yet.
I hope that sand makes Hisham reconsider being a farmer. He should be wielding that old spiked mace of his rather than a shovel.
Daggerfall! I can't believe I'm here. I've read stories, but the city itself is inspiring. I can't wait to go exploring. I think I made the right choice.
It feels good to be on a ship again. There's still much I can't remember, but I feel like being on the open sea will help.nnI'm glad you found me when you did.
Please hurry. The Daedra kept my squad alive for a reason, and it can't be a good one.
She's going! We'll be safe now! Truly, you've saved us twice-over.
Comrade.
I had hoped my days of being around Covenant soldiers were far behind me.
You must tell <<Ac:1>> what killed her husband.nnTry to stand to the side, just beyond her reach. A simple precaution.
You turn your back on my people? You are dead to me! Dead!nnGo and be with your Wood Elf friends .
To think the Mane would betray us like this.
You've returned! And the Mane is here, unharmed! Jone and Jode are looking down on us.
Move with purpose, slowpaws. Only the fleet of foot survive.
<<1>> will belong to the sea itself before we hand it over to the Maormer! This entire summit is a waste of time.
<<1>> and <<2>> returned just after the skies cleared up. They're a bit damp, but otherwise all right.nnMy lookout says I have you to thank.
Thank you for making your services available. I'm confident we can resolve this amicably.
There's much work to be done, but the people of <<1>> are up to the challenge.
Thank you for sending her away. I don't know if I would have felt safe  if I would have felt safe for Lothiel with her in town.
Mercy, please, mercy! Save me from this madwoman!
Move. Unless you don't mind the spatter.
I wonder if you weren't sent by Y'ffre herself. I hope so. nnWe can't let these Hollow drive us away. We have to hold this ground. We have nowhere else to go.
This one is honored to know you, Grand Champion. Balag looks forward to seeing you fight in future days.
Congratulations. Your performance was positively inspiring. Perhaps you aren't the greenhorn you appear to be.
I've wasted decades studying Ayleid wells, and I know less now than I did when I started. I'm ready to give up.
Y'ffre's knees! I didn't expect to find you in one piece.
You're full of surprises, lovely. And aren't you the strong one?
With armies marching across Cyrodiil, I pray our priory will be left alone. But war seldom spares the innocent.
Back off
Can you hear the crowds? They still chant your name! They thirst to see more of you, Grand Champion!
Our scouts say the Hollow have stopped fighting. Some have crumbled into dust. Others have simply wandered off.nnI trust this means you destroyed the Watchman?

I recognize you from Indaenir's description. He said you'd be coming this way.nnHe had hoped to be here to greet you himself, but he seems to have wandered off again. Regardless, we need your help, if you're willing to offer it.
The bindings  they feel brittle  less powerful .

Thank you for sending those scribs my way. They mean no harm, they're just skittish from the hurricane.nnWith no scribs to protect, the big ones will settle down. Looks like you saved the whole brood.
I hope Asvorn will help me out of this pit. I can't take this much longer.
When Tertius gets back, he's going to be mad about what they've done to our house. I just hope he finds Donus.
What have you done?
Now what?

Praise Y'ffre! The miasma has cleared. Yet I sense this begins a new chapter for the Great Tree.nnThough the creatures gorged themselves upon its roots, this was a passing instinct. They can be taught to strengthen the Great Tree.
Chorrol's been through a lot. But we're tough. We'll keep rebuilding, no matter how many quakes and monsters hit us.
You saved my life. For that I will always be grateful.
The Divines bless and keep you on this glorious day!
Elsenia told me what you did. You can't know how grateful we both are that you brought us back together.

There is little we can do to help our fellow Ash'abah here now, so we should do as my father wished.nnWe should dedicate ourselves to destroying the Withered Hand. They killed my father; I will enjoy the opportunity to even the score.

Go. Find Tzik'nith to the northwest. She shall open the way to the tower for you.nnWe shall remain here for now, guarding the Wood Elves' tree. They shall pay dearly to get it back, and my people shall reap the profits!

You're insane to want to go down there. Go speak to Kargand if you won't change your mind. He's led the rest of the Mages Guild contingent into the Hollow.nnYou'll find nothing here but darkness and creatures born of it.
I know Hannura will like the fish. Cold-water fish are her favorite.
You looking for someone in particular?
You're back! Tell me everything! Did it go well? Were you able to convince them?
We must find the key. One of these muskarse smugglers might have it.
We need to get moving. This one knows his sister is alive.
Don't ever become successfulit's a killer. Gathering herbs and delivering them all over Cyrodiil is going to be the death of me yet.
I felt the magicka shockwave from here. I take it you destroyed the Engine?
Look, the vapor is clearing up! I don't know what you did, but it worked!nnI'll let you tell <<1>> the good news.
My shipmates're gone. Guess they're rebuilding the ship now.
We're on an island, and they have a temple just for water? Khajiiti aren't what I expected.
I've not heard from my foreman for some time. I fear there is trouble at the docks.
I saw smoke rising from the docks. Something is wrong. I feel it.
Did you close the door behind you? Check it again. I heard screaming.
Stay back, wanderer. You are welcome to our camp, but our chief is not entertaining guests.nnLike so many of our warriors, he has been poisoned. Only his daughter may disturb his rest.
I hear you're going to match wits with the Mad God! I don't envy you. nnMight I suggest looking over my wares before you go? You never know what you might need in the Daedric realms.
An undead scourge shambles from beneath the waves and the mighty Redguards drop their swords. It's either folly or cowardice. I can't decide which is worse.

My people's pride is maddening. I wish to protect the city, but I may well be killed if I try. It is bad enough that I dabble with the arcaneto strike our honored dead would be an unforgivable sin. You must save my kinsmen from themselves.
Welcome to the Sentinel Mages Guildhall. nnYou have curious look. Masura-dra is thinking you want to join us. Is this so?

My daughter is  not happy right now. She is as stubborn as her mother was, but  death will not be stayed.nnBe assured though, initiate  after you complete the trial, she will help you fight the Hand if you wish.
My brothers and sisters in the Guildhall do not understand why we keep our swords sheathed in the face of the Ra-Netu. It is difficult. But it is a needful discipline, good for fighters such as we.

It appears that Mara has answered my prayers. nnI find myself in a bit of difficulty and I wonder if I could prevail upon you for a favor. A group of notorious bandits sacked the Bravil Chapel of Mara and made off with some holy relics.
Once again, we find ourselves in the Shadow Wood. As unpleasant as it is, I think I'm beginning to understand this place. nnI think I might know how Naemon's Shade is using it to corrupt the Green.
So you made it through the walking corpse pile? Good work. If you managed that, you may be qualified for membership in the Fighters Guild. You interested?
The Chieftess will learn the price of pacifism. Once she's gone, I will begin uniting the tribes - through force if necessary.nnPerhaps one day we'll be strong enough to slay the Wilderking.
Was that an explosion just now?nnSpeak to the Mage. She's been looking for you.

The holding cells are below the Hall of Judgment. The captured mages should be down there. I'll keep the gate clear until you return. nnDon't dawdle, if you please. I'm good, but even I have my limits.
The sun and salt are bad for head injuries. You should get to the encampment in the shadow of those towers.nnAnd don't fall asleep unless <<1>> says so!
Watch out for the scavengers, wildlife or otherwise. They won't hesitate if they see a fresh meal.
I guess you've figured it out, I'm not really here to "research" the Wilderking. Not for some boring book, anyway.
Please, can you hurry? I don't know how much longer I can take this.
It's done. The bastard's dead. Thank you, your help was invaluable.
Get yourself gone, elf-slave. Your Queen has no power here.
Sorry, the lodge is off-limits to anyone not part of the Pact delegation. Don't give me any trouble. I'm not in the mood.
Welcome to <<1>>! Enjoy our delicious fine wines. And don't forget, every day at sun-down we serenade the moonrise.
Well? Did you get me a drink, or are you still useless?
You never cease to amuse me, mortal. I shall continue to watch your progress with great interest.
And now I fade. Where will I go? What realm will I next call home?
Have you found my ring yet? I don't want to return to my mother without it.
You closed the Daedric portal!  Moonhenge is back to its old self, plus a few decorations. But where's the Captain?
Good luck, friend. Save a few ogrims for us. We'll meet you upstairs as soon as we can.
I'm not surprised <<1>> sealed herself in that tomb. Everyone knows how she felt about <<2>>.nnWhen a puppy follows you day and night, it wants the occasional scratch behind the ears. More fool him!
We're lucky we only lost Iniel in that strike.  It could have been far worse.  Thank you for saving my squad.
Hushed voices and furtive glances. This isn't going to be good.
Good luck out there. This one will stay here for a moment. Relax, so that no one says we do not fit in.
It is never a good sign when mages keep plans secret. Azsu knows this.
Thank you for the books, but <<1>> does not want you to forget what is owed!
Glad you're up and about, recruit. I'm in need of a scout to head to <<1>>. Most of our fleet foundered to the west, but we've had few survivors trickle in from that direction.
All of this death is needless.
First the hurricane, then rats from the sea. What next, flying mudcrabs?nnS'rendarr's mercy, we need more time before the inspection!

Was the treethane as rude to you as she was to me? All I asked was how one might get an audience with the Wilderking, but the way she reacted, you would have thought I was trying to slaughter her children.nnDid she treat you any differently?
Good luck.
If you have come to speak with the king, the gods smile upon you, for he is holding court.nnDo not presume to waste his time though. He has urgent matters to deal with, and has no time for trifles.
I am so ready to shake the dust of this place from my boots.
I find it pleasing to take in the air of this city once in a while. Even if it means I must subject myself to the presence of Wayrest's less   desireables.

Did you see that? The Maormer mage had activated the barrier on this door to block us from getting to the Binding Pool, but I figured out how to break it!nnWhat about you though? Did you repair the seals?
Father's breathing grows ragged. This one doesn't know what else to do.
The stench of fried rat heralds your arrival! Are there any eggs left? Motivating tigers is hungry work.
Akkhuz-ri is not surprised that an Eye of Queen Ayrenn will easily accept what happened.

Oh, a familiar face. This one didn't recognize you at first, but you arrived just in time. Tarrami thought we were done for once <<1>> sentenced us to death.nnBut how do we get out of the Hall of Judgment? They're not going to let us simply leave.
Help us please.
Why did I let my brother drag me into this?
This one will make sure Kargand recovers. Thank you for your help in freeing us both.
This body is crude, but it will suffice. Thank you, mortal creature. You won't mind if I make some modifications, will you?
Please get me out of here. I'd  I'd be really grateful.
Are you scouting Fort Rayles? I'd love to see it in Dominion hands!
Hey there, friend! You look exhausted. Take a rest. We're quite safe here. nnThadrig has a mace the size of a ship's mast behind the barnot that I'd have him use it against the ancestors.
If you plan to loot my family's plantation, I will give you such a thrashing!
I thought I saw an old book or something by a skeleton near the panels. Maybe there's a clue in there.
If you stay, the guards will kill you. Makes no difference to me, but I assume it does to you.
Get out of here, shoo! If the guards spot you, I'll have blood stains to clean too.
Beware the guards, friend. They attack without remorse.
Is the Pact attacking Fort Rayles? I hope there's a lot more of you coming.

You have the king's gratitude, wayfarer. News of your exploits has reached the throne. While we cannot publicly condone violence against our honored dead, the fact remains that you have made the city safe. nnAt least for the moment.
The council has discussed what you told us. Debated your words from every angle. Even drew upon Faraniel's arguments from past meetings.nnUnderstand that we did not reach our decision lightly.
Oh, no. Don't tell me there's a Pact army coming. More holes in my walls is what that means.
Keep your head down, friend. The guards will attack you on sight.
You address the seneschal of King Fahara'jad's court. Spare me your foreign preambles and tell me your business here.
Watch out for the guards. They attack Pact soldiers on sight.
Be careful. They don't like Pact soldiers around here.
Crude, but effective in your methods. Perhaps you've heard that before.
You again? You are like dung Ishalga cannot shake from her boot.
Is it not enough that you defile our dead? Now you must defile our home as well? Begone.
You are brave to cross my threshold, wayfarer, with your weapons still soaked in my ancestor's blood. I will not have your unclean feet tread dishonor in my home. Please leave.
Sorry, but I must be alone. A Caretaker cannot protect the Vale without peace in his heart.
What am I going to do with you? Possessing this much skooma guarantees a decade in manacles.nnWhat aren't you telling me? How much will you cooperate?
How could you destroy this family?nnWe are ruined. Ruined!
My brother and I will guard this area. See what you can do about those reinforcement portals.
Erunor? Where is he? He's not coming, is he?
You have done well. I will burn an offering to Mara for the souls of my slain companions.
You got my brother out of there alive, and for that I thank you. nnI'm sure Mara will forgive me for saying it, but he's worth more to me than all the relics in the chapel.
Mara be praised, you've returned! Did you find the relics?
Zur's mind feels empty  silent. I miss Gadris already.
Thank you again for your help. For choosing me. But I wish that both Zur and I could have been saved.
I will scout this area and make sure we destroyed all of the Daedra that got through the portal.
There are two portals being used by the Dremora to transport reinforcements. You have to shut those portals down!
Well, that was invigorating! I love killing Daedra in the morning!
Is this my doom, then? To haunt this island, warning others of a danger I could not defeat?nnWhat a miserable non-existence.
Done already? Hmm.
We need trained warriors out on the battlefields, so hurry up.
So soon you've learned all there is to know about siege engines?
I head what you did in Shattered Shoals. Thank you for getting my men out of there.nnAnd I understand you helped the Prowler's crew, too?
This one hopes Ezreba finds a new standing on the Two Moons Path.
<<1>> pulled me out of the brine. Thought I had a grip on my friend, but all I held was this <<z:2>>.
I'm worried about my dogs. I've called them for dinner, but they haven't come.
I hope this was all worth it. I was so looking forward to turning their minds to jelly.
You and the Champions  excuse me, the candidates. You must make for your next challenge. The Moons tell me that your next destination has been revealed to you.
The temple of the Mourning Springs has been set to right. The moonlight shines upon you.

Only the dead and the desperate end up in this part of the desert. You appear to be neither, so you must be a very brave woman. nnDo you intend to enter the cursed grounds, the Tears of the Dishonored?
We weren't prepared for this. The Daedra were too strong, even for our magic. I fear I'll never leave here.
He will not remain discorporated for long. His consciousness will be adrift for a few moments, but that is all.
Back again? What else would you like to know?
target: Gi tornato? What else would you like to know?

source: Cannot one set up a simple shop in peace? A ghostone swears it was a ghost, haunting the lower platform.nnOh, my shop!
You have your orders. Move along.
Anxiety parches my skin. Too many demands, too few supplies. Are you here to sooth or irritate?
Done already?
You've already been through enough training, warrior, so get out onto the battlefields and help the Covenant take Cyrodiil.
If you're not going to deliver those to Bugbesh, I'll take them back.
Done already?
Destroy those binding totems while we complete the ritual.
Nasty business, these rats. It is a good thing we have so many cats about. Little pests never stood a chance!
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
I think you have a fight you need to finish first.
Too weak to move .
You saved me from a terrible predicament. nnI wish you'd been around when I accidentally dropped that slop bucket on the Khajiiti wizard.
I thought I saw a book or something by a skeleton near the panels. Maybe there is a clue in there.
I thanked you for saving me from the crocs, and now I can thank you for saving our holy relics.nnMara bless you, my friend.
We were waiting to make sure you made it out. I'm glad to see you safe and sound.
It is interesting, yes? Shazah read for so long, she studied so hard  and yet I still feel like I was unprepared for this. She is very grateful she had you at her side, Hallowed.
Your bravery and spirit impresses even Khali. Truly you are the Hallowed. Shazah and I are lucky to have you at our side.

I would love to explore this lost city, but apparently we still have much to do. This planar vortex that Cadwell describes concerns me greatly.nnLet's head inside and formulate a new plan to deal with this danger.
Not bad. You're pretty fast.
You look good. How do you feel?

Aranias wants to see the Wilderking. I'm his gatekeeper. To see him, you ask me nicely and then I tell you a story. A story that you take part in.nnWhen the story concludes, you are invited to see the Wilderking.
The Divines be praised for your safe return.
I hope you've come bearing good news, comrade.
Ra'zaym hopes you have returned with something to report.
Well? Share your news with the council!
By the Green, share your news and be quick about it.
I'm going to pray long and hard to the Steadfast tonight. Ask him for guidance, and patience.
You must be here for the Trial of Spirit. Know that I am the Loremaster of Haj Uxith. I maintain the traditions and customs of my people.
Are you here for the Trial of Spirit? Then know that I am but a humble farmer, dealing with whatever this strange land throws at me so that I can provide food for my people.
Ah, I see the Trial of Spirit has begun. I am a go-between. I negotiate interactions between my people's two factions, as well as with the other inhabitants of Coldharbour.
I cannot believe this! He should not be here!nnAnd how can she go through with this when he made us wait so long?
The moonlight illuminates each of our paths and guides us to where we could go. Did the moon shine similarly for you?
What's this?
What's the delay? Let's get out of here.
Mages always have to talk at the end of the world.
Please, help Vanus.
Thank the Green you could see the relics into Felari's hands. To think, if these lives had been lost for nothing.
Are you from the Covenant army? I didn't expect you quite this soonand frankly, we're not ready.
Make haste, now. My students and colleagues have travelled far, and we don't have time to waste.
Have you killed those wolves yet? It's vital that you do!
You've done so much. Helped us  what have I done?
We're all accounted for. Good. And now for the final step.
Now there's just one more thing, but it's a doozy.
This is dishonorable.nnBut perhaps necessary.
This one has work to do. Warlock Carindon can answer your questions.
By the tip of my staff, this place is fascinating. The flora and fauna are remarkable. And probably dangerous.
Pain is a small price to pay for the lives of two Guild Mages.nnThis one's lucky we don't off him like we did his friends.
I'm starting to think that studying in a dusty basement somewhere would be preferable to this place. Let's go.
Let's get moving. I hope the Bosmer are open to conversation.
This isn't going to bring Patraud and Ahainar-jo back, but if we don't get some information out of this Bosmer, their deaths are meaningless.
I'm not going to get up on your account, if that's all right.
The Dominion's enemies strike from within and without. It makes allies like you all the more precious.
Welcome to the fellowship hall. You're not from Bergama, though. Are you from Sentinel? nnNo matter, as long as you're a Forebear.
Welcome to the Bergama Crown Fellowship Hall. I do not recognize you, but I see you wear the formal dasha. nnI trust you are a Crown from outside the city?
Have you bones for I?

Patraud was a good man. That attack  was unfortunate.nnBosmer can be aggressive, but killing without provocation is rare for even the most feral of their kind. The sooner we find this spirit, the better.
Are you new to Bergama? Many of our fellow Forebears have been abducted while the Magistrate does nothing. nnKeep your blade near to hand. You may need it.
Greetings, kinsman. nnPlease, abide a while. You should avoid the street. Crown dogs masquerading as bailiffs patrol in force.
Take heart, kinsman. Though Sentinel struggles under the Forebear king's yoke, Bergama thrives  or at least it did. Be cautious.
You've done a great service to the Bosmeri and Khajiiti people. A proud service.
Haven't you a home of your own? Go back and suckle at the teat of your Magistrate.
Honor to you and your house, traveler. If it is knowledge you seek, the Guild can provide.

It is good that the Redguard factions are feuding. Were they not so hostile to one another, the Guild would certainly be blamed for the recent disapearances. nnRedguard vengeance is  severe. We are wise to keep our distance.
<The body is pale and lifeless. His features mark him as the source of the construct you met above.>
<The Spinner lies silent and still.>
There are people burning my island. I can feel it burning.
The chains behind me are like tree roots. I cannot pull free.
Greetings, wayfarer. Bergama is a grim place these days, but the Guild Hall always welcomes comrades in arms.
Welcome, walker. Grand Warlord Sorcalin has given me her orders. They can be found on the boards alongside me. Good hunting!
Hail, wayfarer. I apologize for my sparse stock. Many and many of my horses have borne my countrymen to safer cities. I find myself coin-rich and horse-poor for the first time in my life. A pity.

You do me great honor entrusting me with this Ansei Ward. I promise you, for as long as I live, it will not fall into enemy hands again. nnNow, only the final Ansei Ward remains  but if Uwafa and Alasan are gone, who has it?
<You find a bottle of foul-smelling liquid in this pot.>
Please. This one does not need trouble. Take what you need, and go.
Buy what you need and move on.
Yes, yes. The cats hold the city again. What can I do for you?
Ah, good to see a friendly face. Do not let the soldiers scare you. They will behave under Zetisha's roof.
It feels as if a light is piercing the fog. Perhaps I could fire up my forge again. nnI loved crafting weapons and armor. People came from all around to commission my work.
I'm so happy I could just sing!
Drink will help with the fear. Try some?
Mahirr has done as the soldiers asked. Do not ask him to do otherwise.
My students are busy right now. Try another time.
Hallowed, the Queen already has plans to make use of us again. Speak with her, if you would.
I'm just trying to sell some goods here, yeah? What can I do for you?
Ahh, the sweet smell of peace. It fills my nostrils like a fine boquet.
Tinti only sells to Eagle. No exceptions.
Be cautious! There are some here not friendly to Pact soldiers.
Look. Buy. Move on.
The waters of Cropsford run swift and deadly for Pact soldiers. Tred carefully here.
The guild is neutral in this conflict. Muzuli is only here to train who would hear her words.
Well, this should be interesting. You seem to be a little short on friends around here.
I've never seen such cowardice. These cats rolled over at the first sign of trouble. Bah! Sell you something?
I'm just trying to make a living here.

More brave soldiers arrive soon from Marbruk. We will rally them here and prepare to launch a full-scale attack.nnWhen your task is done, light the beacon in the lighthouse. That will be our signal to charge in and drive the bastards back to the sea.
We fought so hard for our people. To see him dead by my own hand .

This one and his beloved mate sought shelter, but there was none to be found. Ernabi, she didn't make it. Now I lack the will to go on.nnOur children will grow up without parents. They will be poor and destitute and probably die young and alone.
Go! I don't matter. Ayrenn's all that matters now. Save the Queen!
You destroyed the <<1>>, didn't you? I feel different somehow.
I appreciate that you came to get me. A little longer and who knows what Drasilla would have made me do!
Get out of here! I command you to  just go.
No, I'm afraid I can't let you into the story. Your character's been killed, for one.nnOh, I'm sorry. Andur refuses to leave.
Hail, wayfarer. Be welcome and drinkbut not to excess. Forebear treachery runs canyon-deep here. You must keep your wits about you.
No, I haven't been slipping out at night to shank a few of these bastards. Why do you ask?
Hungry? Abject terror will do that to you. I run here every day now to avoid being kidnapped. nnIf you want my advice, stay indoors. There's Crown mischief everywhere.
Welcome to the Stone Oasis, O wayfarer. nnWe seek no trouble in this placethe streets are dangerous enough. So please do not show your blade.
Now that I have the designs back in hand, the question is how soon can we get the town cleared, and get people back to work on the ships?
Blasphemy! The Elder Scroll of Mnem has been stolen from our temple. I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but you will not feel their holy presence until our scroll returns.
I prayed Tu'whacca would guide you.nnDid you find Zariya?
The Justice always treated me so kindly. How could he do such a thing?
Istah. I might have known. nnMay Onsi pluck the tongue from his perfidious mouth. It will make bitter meat for the vultures.
Thank you for your assistance, wayfarer. nnThough the thought that I was serving a traitor like Sulma is sour as milk from a rotting goat.
Istah in the stocks? This whole affair reeks of treachery. The asps responsible will be put to heelno matter how high they slither.
How could the Dominion have lost Brindle? Heads should be on pikes for that!
Aranias wants to see the Wilderking. I'm his gatekeeper. To see him, you ask me nicely and then I tell you a story. A story that you take part in.
I'd feel safer if Brindle were back in Dominion hands. I hope you're here to make that happen.
Our Justice heaps shame upon himself and all of  Ruptga's children. nnMay his bones bleach and our memory of him fade.
Istah is in the stocks? I cannot believe a Crown could commit so heinous a sin.
You returned the Great Mage to us. For that, you have my thanks.
Aye, this'll do just fine.
A Crown Justice engaging in petty barbarism? nnI'm shocked, truly. See how shocked I am?
What now? Let Klovag know I'm waiting for him.

I have heard that Justice Istah has been placed in the stocks. They say he has done the kidnaping, but Tall Papa's whisper tells me he is accused unjustly. nnNow I will have to turn to one of the bailiffs to find my son. Tu'whacca aid me.
<<1>> heard about what happened on Viper Island. Those Maormer, they are not natural, yes? Just thinking about it gives me the shivers.nnYou have the spine of Alkosh to face such things!

Such a terrible thing, this storm. Dashed the armada to pieces, or so I've heard.nnIf the family fleet weren't in such a sorry state, we'd consider lending a hand. As it is, all we can do is hope for the best.
We've been pursuing the Maormer from Auridon. Who knew they had such a foothold here within the Valenwood?
That Indaenir. He's quite a character.

Thanks for saving those miners! I'm sure they'll tell everyone they meet that my sweet trolls didn't really mean any harm. I can't wait for my sweetums to come back to me. We'll return to the arena in triumph!
Kargand is showing signs of improvement. This one thinks he will recover with time.
Istah burns in the stocks and still Sulma conspires. Something is terribly wrong here.
Have you heard they arrested Justice Istah? I wonder which bailiffs agreed to apprehend him.
Is that everything? My pipe, the wine, the delicious pork yes, this will do just fine! You Dominion soldiers are useful folk.
This whole thing stinks. I've watched that Justice for months. If he's crooked, I'm a horker. nnThat Magistrate is hiding somethingand I think I'll find out what it is.
My friend, before you go, Raz would tell you: he leaves now to travel to Senalana, an Ayleid ruin west of Arenthia. The Colovians are still fighting to hold those old stones. This one must know why.
The Justice dishonors all Crowns with such barbarism. Tu'whacca will judge him harshly when Istah dies, I assure you.
By the Eight! I'm so glad to see another living soul!

It is vitally important that we take the Chasm. If we fail, we'll never be able to cross into Molag Bal's inner sanctum and reach the portal to the planar vortex.nnCadwell will aid you. He sees the world in a different way, but he's a good man.
Very impressive. Shazah and Khali are lucky to have someone like you as their guardian.
Yes, hello. Unfortunately, I have no time to chat. I own a busy and prosperous mine. Can't get behind in my paperwork.
Istah thumped me for "public drunkenness" once. I say, whats the point of private drunkenness? Those're the folks with real problems, right? Right?
Well done, Hallowed. I know the Queen values your contributions to the Dominion.
I forsee great things in the Khajiiti people's future. It's an honor to have been present for such an important ritual.
Well done! I have every confidence that you're the Moon Hallowed these women need.

So Istah's been clinkity-clanking around in his shiny armor kidnaping folks and hiding their bodies? Alone? I don't buy it. nnEither way, Samhudah's still paying me a fortune to stare at a door. So all's well in Mauloch's eyes, eh?

My father sent me away when he found out that I helped you. He couldn't bring himself to end my life, even though that's what the sentence called for.nnI've never felt so alone before. What I did though  it was right. It had to be done.
We've done it. We've completed the Two Moons Path. It's all over now.
They've put our Justice in the stocks. Akatosh help us. His bailiffs are even more inept than he is.
Why haven't you talked to that other Argonian over there yet?
Poor Istah. Such a stout fellow. nnHe never really extended the hand of friendship to Uncle Thakh, though. Perhaps his successor will be more  sociable.

My killer comes to humiliate me once again? Well, know that your luck won't help you here.nnI do hope you compete in this game. I so want to get another chance to rip out your heart and pull out your spine!
I'm glad that the Imperial has found someone else to talk to. His haughtiness is suffocating.
Scourge take them! The Elder Scroll of Chim has been stolen! I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but you will not feel their holy presence until our scroll returns.
I knew that Crown Istah was untrustworthy, but to murder that many people? nnIf he would only confess it would probably go easier for him.
I heard that that oafish Justice was arrested. What a delightful irony! I've been on his list of suspects for some timeI just know it.
You have what I asked for?
Thank you. I'm free again, finally. Time to leave this blasted cave. I hope whatever it was you were hoping to happen does, in fact, happen.

Wait  I know you. Why do you continue to hound me? Didn't you already celebrate your little victory with the pretty little princess, Ayrenn?nnDon't tell me you've entered this contest, as well? How  intriguing.
Again you remind me of the monster that I am. You defeated me in life, what more do you ask of me?nnWhat do you hope to accomplish by showing up here again?
Truly, I hope we never need change a story so extensively again. Though we spinners can do so, it's usually better to let a tale conclude on its own.nnUsually.

What foul magic is this? It's as if we've been plunged into a realm where the blight has taken over. Did you hear that voice? It referred to this as the "Shadow Wood."nnWhatever it is, it's not good. Not good at all.
She seemed very upset. Very upset!

Aranias was guided here to take my place, but I believe you were guided here to assure her ascension.nnIf you had not come, I fear Andur would have killed us both, leaving the Valenwood wild and vengeful. Many lives would have been lost.
You shall find her in the tunnels below.

I'm scared. Shouldn't I be feeling confident? I mean, we defeated Andur.nnLook at all of this though! I've worked my magic on small pieces of land in the Summerset Isles  but this is an entire forest  a living forest. Tell me I can do this.
There, you should be able to get inside without trouble now. Be mindful of the Worms inside  they are a dangerous lot, as you well know.
What? Are you one of <<1>>'s thugs come to harass me again? You want your arm broken, too?
We came far too close to a tragedy here. If we'd wrongly slain Alanya .
Back to training for me. Maybe if I ignore them, these louts Gudarz has brought in will go away.
The Elder Scroll of Alma Ruma has been stolen! I can tell you of the Elder Scrolls, but this temple is an empty shell until our scroll returns.
I'd probably be a stew if it hadn't been for you. Thank you.
Once you put the boot to that spineless Nord we can finally have our camp back.
You don't look like one of these flea-bitten bandits. Have you come to join the actual militia?
Travel to the Labyrinth and stop Aranias.
Istah's collusion with those Forebear dogs has finally born its bitter fruit. May Tu'whacca show him mercy, for we Crowns will not.
This would be quite a charming view if not for all these oafish Crowns muddying it with their drab attire and sour faces. I honestly have no idea how they live like this.
Don't mind me. You seem a bit busy. We can talk later.
We should be wary. The way is guarded.
You know what's best after such a fine meal? A nice soak! The water in our pools is just exquisite!
Take your time and freshen up. The celebration in honor of Stibbons will be starting shortly.
I never thought that nightmare was going to end. Thank you for helping us.
Why should I talk to you?
These little militia bugs do a good job of keeping our camp going, gonna be sad when we run the last of them out.
Isn't it nice that the militia is giving us this camp?
I'm getting real tired of these militia rats.
Stop looking at my tusks. Stop it.

Now that we don't have to worry about overwhelming hordes of reinforcements, we're sending in the main assault force.nnWhile they keep Molag Bal's minions busy, you need to navigate the Labyrinth and find the portal to the planar vortex.

Have you selected a companion to accompany you? If you need more time to speak with your friends, please take it. This might be the last chance you get.nnWhen you're ready, I'll give you final instructions and we can begin our final assault.
Something's changed. I do not understand what is going on here.
The Fighters Guild is ready. We're prepared to follow you into the very heart of Molag Bal's lair.nnWe shall not fail you.
Well, I won't say that wasn't at least a little entertaining, but we're not finished yet.nnTime to enter the Labyrinth, old friend.
Let's tear this coward apart! Let's make Molag Bal wish he had never been born!nnWait a minute. Are Daedric Princes born? It doesn't matter! He'll wish something when we're done with him!
My people have been used and abused by the Lord of Brutality for long enough. Tonight, Molag Bal will feel the full ferocity of my mighty warriors.
Mistress Kauzanabi-jo will set you on your path, Hallowed. Good luck.
Listen to this, Kireth: "Reach out and touch a brazier to draw forth the fire and launch it in the direction of your choosing."nnHow fascinating! I wonder what it means?
Why do Daedra never install guardrails? It's like they want Zur to step into the bottomless chasm and fall to his death.nnZur has mentioned how much he hates heights, yes?

I recognize these devices. I've researched them. Even written reports about them. Never saw one in person, though.nnThey are marvelous to behold. Only a god could craft an artifact of such brilliance.
I'm ready to show the Dark Lord a little brutality of my own!
I promised to help you if you helped me, and here I am! I do not regret what we did to liberate my clan, and I never will.nnDo you smell that? That's the smell of freedom. And it smells wonderful!
You need someone to accompany you into the Dark Lord's lair? You freed the lamias from our prison, let me help free you from yours.
The Crown of Bones' power will grant us victory this day!nnI can't wait to see what treasures await us inside the Endless Stair.

This is so exciting! I sat around in a drunken stupor for so long, it feels so good to be finally doing something!nnOf course, we are going up against Molag Bal. Maybe I picked the wrong day to stop drinking.

You were a worthy opponent in the Orchard. I'm almost disappointed that we must now fight alongside instead of against each other.nnStill, the Crimson-Matron has sent me to honor your agreement, and I shall not fail you.
Ah yes! Did he find you? You must go to Tava's Blessing at once to help the prince!nnOh, and speak to Captain Rawan, tell him to send Shiri back here right away. Whether she wants to come or not!
<<1>> rescued me, though I guess I owe you thanks, too.nnShe seems nervousyou might want to talk to her.

Tava's Blessing is where the royal navy has its shipyards. You must not let the town fall to the Withered Hand.nnBeware of the shifting sands, wayfarer. I hope Rupta guides you quickly to the prince's side.
Get on with itI can't do anything until you distract my father with a challenge.
We won't be able to use the portal until someone destroys those focus stones.
Another ally is always welcome! Join us! They will not take usnot alive, nor dead!
The matchmaker's interesting. He could sell scales to an Argonian, if you ask me.
Get out of my camp, while you still can.
If it's equipment you want, talk to Elthras. He makes the deals around here.
We won a necessary victory for the Dominion today, and we have you to thank.

I'm getting ready to cart this mead to the Vinedusk Rangers, at the village northwest of here. Everyone here thinks they're crazy, but I've been carting mead to them for ages. As long as they keep buying, they can be as crazy as they want.
Off to adventure in this cave full of bloodthirsty spiders, are you? Awful brave of you, facing so many monsters. Hope you brought some friends!
The Halls of TormentI've never been there, and for that, I consider myself very fortunate.
It looks like I have a long journey ahead of me.
Your loyalty to the crown will be rewarded, my friend. You have my word.nnI can even make this easier for you. Wear this Imperial Armor, and you should be able to walk around the city unnoticed.
That Zara will flirt with anyone, or anything, but put a sword in her hand and watch the limbs fly.
The information you provided was very useful.
Hail, sister. nnWord has reached us that Talia now leads the tribe. Know that we stand ready to fight, should the shadow fall on Bergama.
May Tall Papa guide you on your walkabout, wherever your journey takes you.
I am extremely pleased to see you. nnI always thought the Imperials were civilized, but the way they've treated us, they're absolutely swine!
Praise Zeht! I can no longer abide these infidels!nnDid King Fahara'jad send his army?
Hail, sister. It is good that you have come. nnThe Withered Hand has been hereI can feel it. Stay vigilant.
You there! The Maormer attacked <<1>> with their Sea Viper forces. We need every able body for the rescue effort!
Thank the gods. I hope you're not too late. More Imperials are coming into Satakalaam every day. nnWe need to take back the city before they dig in.
Perhaps someday we will no longer feel the need to fight each other so readily. We shall see.

You filthy dog! You can hurt me if you wish, but I swear, you will pay for attacking our city nnTu'whacca's Breath! You are not one of them. Did the king send his army then? These Imperials could launch a full invasion if they are not stopped.

Despite the armor, it is obvious that you are no Imperial, and I rejoice that you have come to my rescue. nnThe Imperials have mistreated me, but I deemed it likely that they would seize control of all Alik'r, and there would be nowhere to flee to.
This one will be the next champion. Stay out of my way if you don't like the sight of blood. Especially your own.
I understand why you did what you did. In time, I hope my tribe will as well.
Bless you, traveler. I hope I said nothing to offend you.
Fight or begone. I have no patience for unhatched eggs.
Very good! That is all of the tears. This one is finally done with this nightmare-scape of Dremora and beautiful, though terrifying, bodies of water.
No end to these winged rats. Not that I'm complaining! Every feather's worth a fortune in gold to us now!nnYou one of the magistrate's charges? I'm only shooting the ones in town, don't worry.
I've lived in this town for almost thirty years. We've never had any problems with the harpies in all that time.nnSomething foul's on the wind. I know it.
Well, it is good you took the lid off when you did. It was getting stuffy in there.
You must leave now. What transpires next is between Hircine and myself.nnThank you.
Keep under cover if you want to stay clean and dry. The harpies know no end to their wicked deeds.
Go on in. I'll climb up the building from the outside
target: the harpies won't hurt me. Meet me on the balcony with whatever you find.

source: The troops can handle reclaiming the sanctuary, but we can only really end this if we cut off the head. Vicereeve Pelidil is getting further away from us every moment we delay.
Keep an eye out for my soldiers. I'm sure they'll help you hook some Fish Elves.
Give those Maormer a few kicks to the shin, would you?
I'll be right behind you.
This place sounds great! My brother says you can buy anything there. And I mean anything.
This one has heard some dark words about Pa'alat's master. He does not know if this Krin Ren-dro can be trusted.
I bet with both flywheels turning, we can get into Molag Grunda's lair.
You should get out of here! This town isn't safe for Daggerfall soldiers.
You must be a scout for the Covenant. Tell your commander that Therich Rorielle will be happy to see the Daggerfall banner fly over Castle Brindle!
Welcome to the tribe, brother. The wisdom of the Chief was deep as a well. I know his faith in you was deserved.

At least it's over now. We stopped the blight from spreading and defeated Naemon's servant  but at such cost.nnI worry about our decision to sacrifice the Eldest's Heart. Its absence will be felt, and without a replacement  well, I don't know.
You scouting Castle Brindle? I wish the Covenant would hurry up and take it!
You draw the sword for us all, sister. True honor need  need not be named.  Avenge us.
Just get out of here, out! You'll bring the guards down on us!
You bear the tribe's burdens now, brother. Remembertrue honor need not be named. Seek not fame or glory, only justice.
Do not look upon me with pity, sister. Hearts such as ours, crowded with great and terrible purpose, have no room for such things.
Fill this poisoned cup with our enemies' blood, sister. All of the Alik'r watches you. May Tava speed your passage.
Word swirls through camp like a dust devil. So you are Ash'abah now? That is good, sister. nnTrue honor need not be named. Send the Withered Hand back to Oblivion.
Welcome to the tribe, sister. I regret we have nothing to give but our blessings.
Both Zamyad and Parvenah took to the Far Shores during your trial, sister. I fear we will lose even more swords yet.
If you spot Donus on the way to Cheydinhal, please tell him I'm out here, looking for him.
True honor need not be named, sister. May your blade never go thirsty while these fiends still draw breath.
Go through the portal. We'll make sure this area remains secure.
Take the portal up to the next level. We'll take care of any Dremora stragglers who decide to cause trouble.

Hail, sister. The poison of Morwha's Bounty has run its course, thank Ruptga. It would take ten and ten to keep me from my work. Rumor swirls across the dunes. Some say there is a vampiric curse staining Leki's Blade, and now we have found proof.
True honor need not be named, sister. My son's sickness broke while you took on the crucible. You are indeed blessed by the Divines!
All praise to Ruptga: it appears my brother will recover. I take your arrival as a gift, sister. Divines willing, we shall fight beside you soon.
Ah, I love that song.
We've gotten the troops to this point, but we've failed to take the Citadel.
We've come too far to be stopped by a few walls.

Ah, little mortal! While it might be entertaining to watch you bumble about the Citadel, I would much rather just see you get about your business.nnI'm sure that whatever you have planned will ultimately work in my favor.

Cadwell says that the area beyond the pyramid is known as the Labyrinth. We'll need to go through there to reach the Endless Stair and the planar vortex.nnJust keep your wits about you. The Valkynaz is a dangerous opponent.
I knew you'd be able to deactivate the wards. The Fighters Guild troops have already begun our two-pronged attack.
Please let my Brielus know I'm all right. He'll be so worried about me.
Indaenir's waiting for you down in Verrant Morass. He's looking into a blight. I've seen some of the Bosmer from that area, and let me saybetter you than me.
You're back! Did you find everything?
I'm hoping to fight in the Summoner Division, but Tholbor's really picky about who makes it to the final rounds.

I know what they're planning!nnThrough my Psijic projection, I observed an old ritual site north of <<1>>. The Sea Vipers summoned a powerful creature known as a storm atronach. They're funneling all that energy into their bound <<z:2>>.

It seems the necromancer Alasan underestimated you  I was hiding outside the lighthouse.nnAfter you disrupted the ritual, I went in and found Alasan's notes. I think I know where the Withered Hand has taken the third Ansei Ward.
Go to Woodhearth. Trouble stirs from our common enemy.
The Wormies must be here for what's under the Barrowbough. With enough of the little skeletons, they'll be able to dig up the big ones.nnI knew I shouldn't have said anything to that <<1>> fellow.
You'll find Ugorz in the Orc stronghold to the east, and Zirani in the Khajiit village in the west. Both were once-flourishing townshipsbut no longer. They'll need help to escape.
Let's clean these guys out!
I'll be honest, I never expected so brave a plan from a Dunmer. Nor help from a stranger.
By the Green Pact, they're a tenacious lot!nnThe Daedra on the other fronts would have closed on us in that last attack if it weren't for you.
Taskmaster is angry. Taskmaster hates this Khajiit.nnBut Taskmaster hates this Khajiit talking to others even more. Go away, or this one will suffer.
I think you got them all! I haven't seen any wisps in a few minutes.

We must hurry to find the prince. That girl Shirishe is not who we thought she wasshe is heartless. Given the chance, I have no doubt she will kill the prince and raise him as her undead thrall.nnWe must not allow that to happen.
I am Grexev, lord of this border realm of Coldharbour. How pleasant to meet a mortal of your caliber so willing to kill three tormented souls.nnYou would make an excellent Daedra.
Well met, traveler.
Horrible, horrible strangers with sand for souls! May there be no moons in their afterlife!
Sigul-jo is angry. He is right to be so, but it clouds his thoughts and taints his spirit.
Curse every werewolf breathing! This is the last straw, I'm retiring.
Shirithe scholar's apprenticehave you seen her?nnShe had the ancient text from the Withered Hand necromancer at Tava's Blessing  she was supposed to go back to Bergama, but  she never made it.
The pieces are almost all in place.nnWe can move against Molag Bal whenever you want. Attack now or gather more forces. The choice is yours.
What happened here? This is terrible. Did the Imperials do this? nnI hope Shiri was not here. Did you find any evidence that she visited?
Thank you for speaking with her. Very kind of you to stick your neck out for a stranger.
