You told Sarolion? I can't believe you told him about how I felt! That wasn't supposed to happen! Ahem. Maybe I should talk to him too.
It's a lovely day for a fight to the death, isn't it?
I hope you win. If you don't, well .. it was lovely to meet you.
I can't believe it. Zara's tasked me with picking flowers, believe that? I'm a swordsman, not a flower girl! nnDamn my tongue, I can't say no to that girl. It's that purr of hers. Damned distracting.
It's good that Naemon's finally put to rest. Terrible what the Veiled Heritance did to him.
It's just as well Naemon's dead. Not to be harsh, but he would have always been a symbol for the rebellious to rally around. Ayrenn may not be perfect, but she has earned our support.
Queen Ayrenn must hear of this.
Remarkable how Valenwood rights itself. We have Silvenar and the Green Lady once more. When they are united, the Dominion will be stronger than ever.
With Naemon and Estre behind us, Queen Ayrenn will focus on Malabal Tor now.
Now to journey to Malabal Tor, another land this one has never seen.
Shazah is enamored with the story, but all Khali sees is the battle missed.
I feel for Queen Ayrenn's loss. She won't show it, but to lose a family member  twice. I can't imagine if I had to lose my beloved a second time.
Damned Heritance. We lost some good rangers out there. They're lucky I can't get near them.
Heh. Don't mind Nara. She's never done well sitting out a battle.nnIn the meantime, this isn't a total loss. Cariel is a beautiful Elf, isn't she?
I'm sure Indaenir will fulfill the Silvenar role admirably.
Indaenir's in there. I hope whatever luck guided you at the Pass watches over you now.
Don't mistake the queen's strength for callousness. She knows what's needed of her, as a leader.
Kauzanabi-jo was wrong about coming here. Hopefully, the twins have learned much from this visit.
We wouldn't have been able to fight all those Daedra without you. Gilraen will want to speak with you.

Thanks for all your help. Those Daedra would have slain us if it weren't for you.nnYou should speak to Gilraenthat Oblivion Gate is still out there, and I'm sure we could use your help to deal with it.
You have done a great thing ridding the sands of the Withered Hand. Take my ward and meet your friends outside.
I swear, no Maormer will make it past me.
Get away! I am safe here - if you want to help someone, help the hostages.
It's hopeless. Satakalaam is lost to us.
Where did they come from? How could they have taken Satakalaam?
Flee this place, fool! The Imperials will slay you, should they fall upon you.
I traveled long and long to reach Leki's Blade. What road do you come by, O wayfarer? I have heard talk of our honored dead rising to slay us. Idle rumor no doubt.
Swordsmanship runs in the blood of all Redguards - but there is more steel than water in my veins. They will erect a monument to me one day.
It has been some time since Master Fadalia joined us at table. I have counted the daysthey are many and many. I wonder who she dines with.
Disciple Tafa says I swing my sword like a woodsman's axe. To Oblivion with that. If it is good enough to fell a tree, it is good enough to fell a man. That is what I say.
I have not seen Peruz since his final blessing. He did not even return to claim his bundle. He simply walked into the desert and disappeared. I hope it was not something I said.

You? You defeated Wildur? He's been our leader for years! This isn't right! You're not even an Ungodly!n nThe rules might say that we have to swear loyalty to you, but to Oblivion with that. We're banditswe break the rules.
I beg your forgiveness, O wayfarer, but I must ask you leave me be. I am entering the most difficult stanza of the swordsman's sun prayer.
Leki speaks to us in this place. Come and contemplate the stones.
Disciple Raifa demands perfection, but tells me nothing! I may as well have stayed in Sentinel.
DiscipleI mean, Master Tafais at least as skillful as Fadalia was. The school is in good hands.
I trained with Milahd for many months before his final trials but I have not seen him since. It is a pity. I was a jackal's whisker away from defeating him in our last bout.
I trained with Milahd for many months before his final trials but I have not seen him since. It is a pity. I was a jackal's whisker away from defeating him in our last bout.
Have you come to honor the heroes of the past? Bring only a stout spirit and a worthy sword, wayfarer. Our ancestors care for nothing else.

I still feel the presence of Master Ahtar in this place. Some have even seen him, if rumor is to be believed.  A passing shadow only, or faint whispers. I hope it is true. Perhaps I will see him someday.
There is power in this place, wayfarer. The spirits here are strong, but heavy with woe. They are well cared for - what could trouble them so?
Weight and balance are key, O wayfarer. Have you taken up a Breton blade? Onsi keep you if you must bear one in battle. Better to wield a boatman's oar, I say.
This way, the interior of the island has a chamber where I can cast the portal.
Some find fulfillment in wielding the sword - I am content to craft them.

Some may call me foolish, but I tell you - the stone fist of Leki's Blade has tightened its grip of late. I sense something cold  blasphemous. A darkness slithers in the heart of Leki's Blade, wayfarer. If only I knew what it was.
Hail, O wayfarer. Unless you're of a mind to step in, leave me be - I've much for which to account.
There you are. I felt embarrassed at my cowardice, sending you back after this thing after I'd fled. I thought I'd come to help you avenge my companions.
Good luck on the road. And come back some time, you hear?
I can't believe it. I thought Throne Keeper Farvad had met a grisly end. nnHe's tough for a priest, a little strange, but tough. I'm glad you managed to find him, and Ansei Radan's Ward.
Welcome to the Guild in Rawl'kha, such as it is.
I am glad you caught up. I am glad you came to the necropolis in the first place.nnTu'whacca says you are the one who must stop Shiri from doing this dark deed.
There, there. We'll be fine now. Fine. You helped us, and when the time comes, we'll help you. Somehow.
Sorry, Razum-dar was lost in thought. The Eyes are getting ready for, uh  something this one is not supposed to discuss.
We were so worried about the alliance leaders fighting among themselves, we never saw this coming.
Are you here for <<1>>? She teaches us how to  to fish.nnYou should speak with her.
Speak to <<1>>, or get out.
Keep walking, Thalmor ear-licker.
You're unwelcome here. Leave this place.

The walk through that tunnel wasn't pleasant. I never realized how much I hate cramped and crowded spaces.nnAnyway, thanks for coming through for us. I was worried we were going to be trapped in here.
All this sneaking and crawling around. It doesn't sit well with me.nnStill, the element of surprise provides a sound, tactical approach to the current situation.
Once the mages are in place, we'll have the Dremora on the run! Nothing clears a battlefield like a barrage of lightning and fire!
Y'ffre's bones! Am I glad to see another traveler on this road!nnPersonally, I can't wait to get out of here. Something really strange is going on here.

Exciting, eh? Beasties with wings, an angry Valkynazyou even managed to befriend a Dremora. Clever, that. nnI made friends with a Dremora once. We had some grand adventures, right until she tried to cut out my lungs. Oh, those were good times!
Please, once they realize I can't pay, <<1>>'s life will be worth nothing to them!
Meet me in the town of Satakalam to the northeast. My vision of the tragedy there is blurry.nnI fear what the details may show.
The hide and my death approach. Please, let me see the white before all goes black.
I shouldn't blame Erinel for leaving. What we had was wonderful, but it was hard, trying to please everyone. I can see how her new life is much simpler.

I'll guard the portal and make sure we maintain control of this location. I may have to take on a Daedroth or two single-handedly, but that's to be expected in my line of work.nnSee if you can't cut off the source of those reinforcements, would you?
Just give me a moment to slip out of these bindings. Don't worry about me going alone, I know this forest as well as anyone.
Do not fear, Nielas. We will make it back safely. Fanrel  Fanrel will be fine without us.
I can't stop hearing Halalin screaming. What were they doing to him? I don't want to know.
Blood for blood. The Wood Orcs have learned what it means to cross the Falinesti Faithful.
Fire has blunted this one's claws May others succeed where I have failed.
Did you not see the smoke? The wise walker would keep far from Dune, yes?
Can claws even catch fire and ice? If the Mages Guild cannot save Dune  what then?
Intriguing place, isn't it? nnWhen you get there, look for Nara. I think she's in charge of the small band that went there.
There is nothing to be done. For every Daedroth felled by one of our warriors, two more emerge. It is all too much to witness, especially for unclawed dung such as myself.
A troupe of valiant warriors, an army, with claws and swords and spears - this is what was sent for and for what Shimsamu awaits. We must hold strong, but without such aid Dune is lost, no?
I'm certain the <<z:1>> will let you bypass the lightning bonds.nnMake those filthy Maormer pay for what they did to us.

We are safe here, at least, outside of the notice of Oblivion and whoever called it upon Dune. Many of us here are not walkers of the Two-Moons Path, though. This one wonders if a rabble of merchants unsound in body and spirit can survive this mess.

The dung life heaps upon this one is just too much! You might think, when traveling with your wares, that this thing or that thing will sell for quite a price to the merchants of your home. But nothing can prepare you for a home ablaze!

A walker comes to Dune! Is there anything that can be done for this place? Yanu-ma asks, for she is unclawed in matters concerning Daedra - as are most walkers in Dune, she thinks. All I can do is have food ready for those with claws enough to fight.

Masrabal-dro knows many things, has seen many things. Many daedra emerge from gates in Dune, and situations like this? They tend to work themselves out, this one knows, and has seen in the past, many times. So, this one remains prepared to trade.
Hail, warrior. The guild always welcomes its own, especially when the campaign is going well.nnSpeaking of the campaign Any news?
The guild is always open to fellow mages provided no other disasters fall upon Dune.
So many people! When did our quiet little city become a metropolis? But business has been good.
I'm not sure I like that we've turned the Hollow City into an army camp, but I can't complain about the increase in business.
Thanks to the stable portals, for once I'm in no danger of running out of supplies.
I think I liked this place better when there were only five of us living here.
Have no fear, citizen! The Fighters Guild is open for business!
Even far from everything we know, some things remain the same. Potential candidates, curious and adventurous. You should consider joining the Mages Guild.
Come, wayfarer, and abide a while. nnWe must enjoy these times of peace before those Gold Coasters come back.
By Onsi's bright blade, if one of those stinking mercenaries lays a hand on me, I'll split him like a dried gourd.
Those damned harpies made off with another of my ponies. By Saint Alessia, another week of this and I'll be walking back to Chorrol barefoot.
The keg goes dry again. Such is the way of things with these Gold Coast mercenaries. A long day of loafing and bullying makes them thirsty as the desert sand.
You're not one of those thrice-damned mercenaries, are you? My husband has already paid you. Begone from here! Go and eat sand!
Business is brisk. These harpies make bows precious, needful things. Everyone becomes an archer!
Can you tell this one what happens in Dune? She thinks, she sees fire, hears fighting, but no army comes. Who attacks our Dune?

Walker, tell Four-Toes what you have seen? He has heard screams and the ring of steel, and his heart fills with dread for the city of Dune. This one stands in his stall with his wares, if you wish to trade. Better to die with gold in pocket.
Hello, if you'd like something, please talk to Nellor.
I do not know who's doing more property damagethe harpies or those twice-cursed mercenaries. Either way, I've been pumping the bellows like mad.
Whatever has fallen upon Dune, let them come to Kurnamu-do! Here, we have the advantage of terrain. No assailant shall make it past this one's flashing steel!
These damnable harpies! A seamstress of my quality should not be stuck mending curtains!
The sellswords are not as bad as everyone says. Better to have drunken louts for protection than none at all. Is it not so?
The mercenaries seemed so professional when they arrived. It was quite heartening. But they did not keep their true natures hidden for long.

A desperate man turns his back on wisdom. Better to unleash a pack of rabid hounds than for our magistrate to welcome into town cutthroats like the Gold Coast Mercenaries. nnDogs and sons of dogs, all of them.
Of all the places for the harpies to strike, they choose our beloved Kozanset. nnTall Papa help us.
This inn used to be the jewel of Kozanset. It will take months to recoup our lossesmaybe years.
It is good to be out and about. Coldharbour is an inhospitable place, but this one is adaptable.
Harpies, bullies with swords . Fangs of Sep! What other plagues must we weather?
Welcome to the  the  oh, by Zeht's tears, I cannot do it. My inn is ruined!
Those Gold Coasters are nothing but but a pack of yellow durzogs. Mauloch help this town if real trouble comes knocking.
They should set those good-for-nothing Baandari Khajiiti on the bird-women. By Mauloch, they'd probably enjoy it.
Hail and welcome, comrade. Shake off the sand and relax a moment. I'd say you've earned a rest.
You got what you wanted. Now leave me alone.
Magister Zoellene keeps us cloistered while those oafish mercenaries roam the streets. We wield the power arcane. Should we not use it in defense of our neighbors?
Welcome to the Kozanset Mages Guildhall. nnI sense a great deal of magical aptitude in you. Have you come to seek admission into the guild?
What else do you want from me? Blood? Bones?nnYou got what you wanted. Everything else I have is mine!
You forced me to give you what was rightfully mine. What more do you want from me?nnNow let me get on with my work, please.
This one has nothing more to say. This one is very angry with you. Very angry.
Dearest Alexis, I feel so weak now. I wonder if the Taskmaster has any more of that marvelous energy he gave us earlier. It made me feel so  alive!
You look as though you have seen battle, friend. Tell me, did you find Aldolin?
Hm? I am not paying you for companionship. Run along and retrieve the coin we are owed!
Well, I hope you're happy. What's the phrase? Out of the kettle and into Oblivion? Shackled for life to Farwen .

I've heard rumors of this city even while back in Tamriel. A city of Cyrodiil that was one day there, the next day gone. Even the most recognized scholars had a hard time justifying its existence.nnBut here we stand in the lost city itself.
That idiot just blew my cover. I respect the Artisan's skill too much to believe that Hendare could find him, so what's your story?
Oh, good. You made it back! My band owes you a debt of gratitude. It isn't often you meet such selfless travelers here.
You are always welcome here, warrior.
I am here with the Queen. For now, the security of this point and surrounds is my responsibility. Please leave me to it.
I will be glad when all this is over. One way or the other.

I was the first of the advance scouts to Dune. I've heard a lot of violence from the Merchant's Quarter, and I've been seeing a lot of smoke. If you're going in, Y'ffre watch your hands - you'll need the help.
There's no reason for you to wait for the authorities to arrive. I doubt you'll retrieve everything in time.
Talk to Thrush. I'm not here in any official capacity.
I am their most beloved. I can feel that.
I apologize in advance for any delay in service. My apprentice Nidras went upstairs to attend to personal business.
I will await you on the other side of the labyrinth.
Thank you kindly. You'll find <<1>> on the west path into town. Hurry back now.
This one greets you, walker! Feel free to peruse this one's wares, as do so many of the good people of S'ren-ja.nnAnd should you wish a trade, by all means, let us talk.

This one welcomes you, walker!nnYou are invited to peruse this one's cart and goods, to see if there is anything you need!nnOr, at the very least, anything you like. For if you like, you are invited to buy, yes?
Hello there! Please, linger a moment, tell me of your tales.nnI will listen especially well if you are open to trading! What better way to accompany a good story than good food and good coin?

This is one of my favorite caravan routes.nnThings are pretty quiet, usually. Lately, though, it's felt like there's a lot of tension in the places we visit.nnInteresting times make for good pay, I guess.
Keep away from me. It's bad enough that I'm here.nnI don't need types like you distracting me from my work on top of everything.
You've done me a service. I'll make sure that buffoon never sees the inside of Telenger's spellbook. You have my thanks.
You're a bit forward coming into my home in such a manner. Something you need?
Any luck?
My men are itching to soak the sand with Imperial blood. We're just waiting on you. Get those hostages out of the city so we can attack.
We will honor the Ayleid King for his sacrifice this day. We will honor  everyone's sacrifice this day.
Spiders do not worry me. Very large, aggressive ones do.
Whatever you are buying, decide now. I don't have time to waste on just anyone.
If you need food, be quick about it. Don't waste my time.
After you. I shall be right behind you.
You seem surprised, mortal. Did you not suspect my true identity?

I felt too guilty to spend my cut from those evil bandits so I hid it all outside of town. I assure you, I've learned my lesson. You can have it all and I'll be on my way to start a new life on the straight and narrow.
May the Green keep and provide for you today.
Kala must consider how she will find the coin for travel. That brother of mine  never thinking of anything but the moons!
Have you found it? Without Red Mountain Ash, Thalara cannot make Nirnroot wine.

Forgive Split-Tongue his split tongue, please. Though many mock him, he still sees his friends about this tree, here.nnIt is where we tend to meet and talk of our days, walker. Every village must have one, no?

Warm sands, walker. This one invites you to enjoy the shade of our tree and our company, as this one and her friends so often do.nnThis one thinks it is better under the tree when certain merchants are no longer screaming and grunting, though!

Khajiit are friendly enough, I guess. But the little things they do when they talk to younnI don't know, I always feel like they're thinking about eating me. I just don't find them appetizing, so it feels unfair.nnI suppose.
Damn that Molag Bal!
A miserable end to a pilgrimage, walker. This one arrived, to find this Stonefire cult has taken Do'Krin for its own. Moons above, what can be done? What of the Golden Claw?
The situation is far worse than I could have imagined. Maybe we truly aren't safe.
Everything we've done against the Tharns, everything that's happened to our fragile alliance  was it not enough?
Those cultists have certainly made a mess of things, Anil-do has seen. If Anil-do had more five-clawed walkers at his back, Do'Krin could be set aright, and things much better.
Shirai-ma sees such horrible things, even just across the bridge. How can this have happened? The roads were so safe!
You're going to die, milk-drinker!nnYou're going to get lanced through your arse, and you'll die on the arena floor in a mess of your own making, because you're not good enough for this arena!
Come closer,et me get a good look at you.nnI'll need to remember your face for when they haul your body out with the others. So I can remember to check my bets, ha!
Greetings, serjo. Your performance was impressive. I hope when we next meet it is to cross blades  provided I win my chance to fight you, of course.nnTime has yet to yield me this prize.
Stop filthying my air with your breath, or I'll part your head from your neck!

I'm in the wrong division. I keep telling them this but they won't let me change camps!nnIf you get into one of the other divisions, put in a word for me? I swear my arm is worth Malacath's attention.

How did an imbecile like you move before me? What kind of a world would permit this? I'm taking this indignation up with  someone.nnJust you wait. Your bribery or whatever will be exposed, and I'll be there watching you dragged through the muck.
It seems you will contend before I will.nnI hope you keep your head long enough. By the looks of you, yours would be a fine head to be tearing off, heh.
Oh, hello. Have we met?nnI'm still trying to earn my way back to Wayrest. Did you fight?nnI think you fought. Well, if you're still fighting, good luck! I think we'll both need it.

No, no. If you're fighting you can't place any bets.nnThis one has seen it happen, it is considered 'cheating', and the beatings those who do this receive are inspiring to behold.nnVery inspiring, this one thinks - enough to say 'no, never.'
Hmm. Come here, sera. Let me have a look at you.nnI'm considering the guar I'm betting on in this race, you see. You look strong enough. But, well  so does everyone, you see?
Don't worry, Nellor won't be tricking travelers again anytime soon. Thank you for bringing him to justice.
You stirred things up. That race was exhilarating!nnI even saw <<1>> and <<2>> talking! Those jackals haven't spoken for ages.
It's the big winner! After a race like that, a body like yours has got to have a massive appetite. What say you slide me some of your winnings?

Ah, a civilized person. My partner and I are here on the typical business of House Telvanni.nnPerhaps after I've met my merchant we can speak over sujamma, in my tent? It's rare, seeing another Dunmer so far afield.
Fires in the city! Chaos everywhere! It's only by Arkay's blessing that we were not killed simply for being Colovian.
I've yet to read the latest texts. Have you read them yet? Thinking of all those pages makes my eyes hurt.

Honor to you and your house, sera. I'm here on House Telvanni business, what brings you?nnWhatever does bring you, may it be swiftly resolved. This caravan is a mess and its drivers s'wit. It's all I can do not to drown myself in greef.
Gore and glory!nnAny time you need a drink, just come to me. The elf-lovers here wouldn't know a good brew if it boiled their faces off.
Warm sands, walker. This unsleek and unfragrant place is an excellent place to sell your goods. Thus, this one remains willing to trade.

You have some claws, khajiit, this one recognizes that. Do you have all five, perhaps? We shall see as you hunt the walls of Thizzrini.nnStill, you seem sleek enough. Sleek and dangerous. This one is glad for your presence, very  amusing.
What is it? Don't they need your help at the sanctuary? Get moving!
So much death and destruction. I don't know why I'm surprised. I never expected Coldharbour to be a walk in the snow.
We meet again, Vestige. I wish to speak with you on a matter of some urgency.
My poor Sayeed. He had no chance.
I'll get better, I swear.
My poor Jalad. He had no chance.
What have you come for pilgrim? Are you looking for me?
Hello, wayfarer. If I am not mistaken, you are the one I was told to look out for.nnI was asked to relay a message if I were to see you.
Your time here is done. But others still need to talk to you.
Oh! That was close! I almost put an arrow right between your eyes!nnI'm glad I didn't. With so few of us remaining, we need all the help we can get.
If Raz had known you would do so well, he would have scrounged you a nicer reward. Apologies. The Mistral armory is not what it once was.
A coin for a child of the hungy moon?

News of this Indaenir intrigue me. Everyone I've spoken to about him says he possesses a sense beyond even the most talented scoutpowers we do not fully understand.nnKeep him close. I believe he may be more important to us than we now know.

Did one of our scouts find you and send you this way? It doesn't matter, we're desperately in need of assistance.nnIf you are willing to help us, please step inside the cave behind me and speak with our treethane.

You need a citizen to stand in testimony against the accused, as well as physical evidence and a magical omen to bring a case forward. nnI recommend talking to my fellow townsfolk and searching the village for evidence.
I did not mean to hurt anyone! It was just a plant!
I'm eager to hear your findings, advocate.
We stand ready to hear your findings, advocate. I encourage you to ask the suspects about any evidence you've found before making an accusation.

We have always been a close-knit community, and many relationships were tried and fragmented in this ordeal. It will take a while to recover.nnNevertheless, we are at peace with the forest once more, and that's all thanks to you.
You are always welcome here, warrior.
We Thalmor have utmost confidence in your ability to uncover the traitor in our midst.nnWe have set everything in motionall you need do is strike the flint, as it were.
Dark clouds gather over Aldcroft. You don't need magicka to see that. But  sorry. You want to talk guild business, I'm sure.
Learn to control your anger and use it to fuel your most powerful attacks! So ends today's lesson. But then, you aren't in the guild yet.
Crosswych needs a stronger Mages Guild presence. Hmm  oh, excuse me! Sorry, just lost in thought. What can I do for you?
Every town can benefit from the Fighters Guild. Crosswych is no different. You looking to join up and make your mark?
That did make sense, didn't it?
Don't make any sudden moves, or I'll give you wings. Arrow wings. Because arrows have feathers? Ah, forget it.
So you're the common trash that Calastil hired to steal my cane?
You. You're that thief Laurosse paid to steal my husband's dog. I hope the rats eat your eyes when they lock you in the dungeon.
How low Earrastel has fallen, dealing with filth like you to take what he wants.

Oh I know, the whole thing seems rather rash and improbable, doesn't it?nnBut our methods get results. Bring back the rat parts, and we'll have a little rodent scurrying about in no time. Why, it will be almost lifelike!
Still a little sore, but I'll be strong as a mammoth in no time.
I wish you sharp claws and clear night skies in your travels, Hallowed.

Are you collecting junk for Adamiir's little monsters? Good.nnI make little monsters too. See this? It's a ant-fly-worm beast. I mashed them together and added a pinch of Adamir's life juice. It's an adorably gross little guy, isn't it?
Back again, I see. And looking better than ever! I hope you're loaded up with Red Mountain Ash. I can almost taste that Nirnroot wine now. Almost.
My heart lightens to see you again, friend. How did you fare?

Oh! About time you arrived. Listen, Blackheart is down on the shore somewhere.nnHe likes to pace the beach when he's on shore leave. And he doesn't find it funny when I point that out to him. Can you blame me for jumping ship?
Use the portal to take the battle to them! I'll hold the ship.
I just guard the barricade. If you have questions, speak with <<1>>.
<<1>> can answer your questions, citizen.
Did the mammoth escape again? You'd be surprised how such a large animal can disappear so quickly.
You're alive! Does that meandid you kill the troll?
Head to the Barrowbough. <<1>> will get you inside, I'm sure of it.
Can't say where the Albatross will head next, but you're always welcome aboard. None of us will forget what you did here.nnAnd <<1>> won't forget, either.

So Treethane Rolon has you looking into the destruction of the sacred flower. nnI hope you understand this isn't just about a plant. The Green Pact defines us. Our whole way of life is based on it. I hope you take the investigation seriously.
Thank you for returning my commemorative censer. The Dominion brought Erinel and I together. Now if I could only untangle this line
I heard you've been made Pact Advocate. Is this true? nnI want to help in any way I can. The Green Pact is sacred and the person who broke it must be brought to justice.
Oh! About time you got here. Listen, Blackheart is down there somewhere. You're going to have to find him and kill him. I will come find you afterwards.
Did you get it? Did you find the wasp?
May the great tree Brackenleaf hold you in his leafy embrace, fellow-Briar.
Pray at the brazier of your spirit animal and receive Brackenleaf's blessing. Then return to me for the final initiation.
I do not look forward to running through the sewers. There's a smell you can taste.
Have you, by chance, glimpsed an older gentleman wandering these tunnels?nnBalding, paunchy, dressed too well to be gallivanting in the sewers?
I told you not to follow me. I didn't want anyone else to die. Why did you have to follow me?
By the Eight it's cold! I  where am I?
Don't worry. I'm a friend. The disorientation you're feeling is natural. It will pass.nnIt's been a while since Glaras sent anyone here. She's been more cautious since the boy Eringor nearly died.

If you want to join my Briars, then there is one more question you must answer. With which of the spirits of the hunt do you feel most closely alignedthe dark deception of the Snake, the dominance of the Tiger, or the cooperation of the Wolf?
We'll keep watch for another decade. We must be certain they will not return.
Welcome back to Coldharbour, old chum. Jolly good to see you! I was afraid you'd snuffed it.
I wonder what Rurelion would say if he knew I was this close to a Dremora?nnBut to be completely honest with you, she makes me a little nervous.
The power unleashed by that Daedric fireastounding! Imagine the spells I could command if I could harness that energy.
You've done much to help the village. None of us will forget you. But now, I must ask you to leave me to my fate.
Erunor? Where is he? He's not coming, is he?
What jolly good fun! I believe the next stop is the Labyrinth, old chum. Shall we toddle off?
We know what you're trying to do. For what it's worth, I wish you luck with it.
It's better to know what happened to my lovely wife than to spend my days wondering.nnThank you.
Are you prepared for what awaits you?
Have you listened to everything Lord Varen had to say?
Lord Varen is not finished. Heed his words.
Varen still has something to say to you.
It is done, then? I would not have such courage. In my mind, you are a hero for what you have done.

I can't tell you what a relief it is to have your help. I'll stay here for a little while in case you have any questions, but then I'll head back to Shornhelm.nnI'll tell Magister Wulfdis I've dealt with the matter and he'll soon have his relic.
Have I convinced you, then? Are you ready to join up?
Hmm. This one smells some magic on you. Do you not sense it? Maybe Magrus licks your face while you sleep! Ha! nnYou should join the Mages Guild. We have much to teach you, walker.
The Elder Scroll of Ghartok is back in our hands, thanks to the courage and strength of our warriors!
Your father's words nearly bring me to tears, so proud am I to serve a king of such courage.nnGo forth, Sameer. Go forth and make your father proud.
The ring is ours for the time being. Guard it well.
I thank you for not condemning me. Even if you don't believe me, I appreciate the chance to clear my name.nnThough, if you cannot find the thief  I won't think about that yet.
You look like you know your way around a fight. You'd make a good Guild member. Ever consider it?
The Guild is wherever we need to be. One day we'll have guildhouses in every city, but until then, tents will suffice.
Before you ask, yes, Altmer can fight, even here. The Guild welcomes all, and isn't involved in current politics.
Make it quick. The Guild doesn't have time to waste.

There's no denying that some of the workers made some bad decisions. But they're not the one who orchestrated it.nnThey were bribed to administer that poison to the johads. They swore they had no idea it would bring disaster upon us!
What do you say, recruit? Have I convinced you? Are you ready to join the fight?

I can't believe it. You mean Anenya was actually telling the truth?nnThat girl has failed every assignment I've given her. She doesn't have a shred of natural magic ability, but if you have the Tear of Anurraame, I have to admit, I'm impressed.
Hello! Are you here on business for the Guild?
Victims, that's all we are. If you're not in an army, you're prey.
We are ready to depart this world. So that no touch of the abomination remains, please bury our items here and let them be forgotten.
Zaddo sets you on your path. Saifa sweeps the path with branches. Orthoron scurries through the underbrush. And Hadam-do lights the sky above you.
The moons speak to Saifa. They tell her of your journey with the Elves in darkness.
Good to see you again. Sorry, just trying to keep an eye on our friends out there.
Why would the Wood Orcs attack us? What did we do to them?
My father is getting crazy in his old age. What's so exciting about the mundane world?
Welcome to Brackenleaf's Briars!
I'm preparing a feast in your honor. Heart of the snake, tiger and wolf will be served. With a side of frog legs and mammoth tongue. We spared no expense!
Maintenance of our shrines is one of many duties of a Master Hunter. It may seem mundane, but taking care of the shrine is akin to taking care of yourself.
With all six Elder Scrolls in Covenant hands, our soldiers will defeat every foe we face on the battlefields of Cyrodiil!
I have a measure of peace. I have done as much as I could to help my town, to help Rivenspire. nnWe could not have contained that abomination without your aid. I am grateful.

<<AC:1>> was sealed for generations. There are many conflicting tales, but all agree that this was the resting place of <<2>>, a powerful necromancer and student of <<3>>.nnThe tales said nothing about shades.
Stay back. There's only death ahead. Shades boiled out of the ground and fell upon us.nnSo much death.
You made the right choice. Tharn's a snake. You want somebody you can trust at your side.nnCome on. Let's go split some skulls and bring Sai home.
Research. All I want to do is research! Why do I always end up in life-or-death situations?nnEither <<1>>'s cursed, or I am. Shades, boiling up from the ground? What next, trolls in heat?
You made a wise choice. Brains over  whatever it is that Titanborn has to offer.
The time has come for another foray into Oblivion, Vestige. We have one last ally in need of rescue.
Hurts  so much .nnGo away  don't like you  anymore
If you encounter trouble, would you please scream so I know to run?
What shall be, shall be. Only justice can restore our village.
I've learned to brew many things since leaving my home waters. Let my great misfortune whet your thirst.
This is all my fault. Oh, Eranas. I'm so sorry.

Be on your guard. In addition to activating ancient defenses, Montclair has somehow awakened the Ayleid guardians that haunt these ruins. You may have to deal with them as well as you make your way into the first portal chamber.
Either you have faith in the pledges of others, or you see things as they truly are. There is no middle ground.

It feels like there's a cloud hanging over the village. I don't like that, not at allit's bad for life, you see. Inside and outside.nnWho can say what will happen from here? Who could know such a thing?
Lots of arguing in the tribe. I don't like that kind of thing.
Greetings, warrior. Grand Warlord Zimmeron has given us much to do. The Pact needs every hero it can get!

There are members of this tribe who are incapable of considering the ramifications of their actions in the long season.nnThe Bosmer welcomed us as they did for we are two peoples of two saps. We mirror them, as water does the sky.
You listen to Slim-Jah.nnShe knows the truth of things. She will show you.

From what I've read, Argonians are rarely apart from their Hist trees. We couldn't have them plant those eyesores here. Best they're to leave.nnOh, and our stores greatly exceed our needs. Browse freely.
There. That's done. The curse is gone. Now the only danger this axe poses is the sharp end.
I cannot believe it! My sweet Musi led you to my bones, didn't she? nnThat is true loyalty! Musi and I walked these deserts together in life, and even death cannot change that!
Lady Zeli spoke truethe Light guides us through the darkness. We shall overcome this evil, and then the people of Shornhelm shall thank House Tamrith for saving them.
Help! Oh, please, help me! We were attacked. They struck without warning, the backstabbing bastards!
Finally, my child is restored to me! There's still much to be done, but you start with clay before moving on to marble.nn<<1>>, if only you could see how wrong you were.
Useless laybouts. Rank amateurs! It was just a simple list of ingredients. How hard can it be?
My wifewhere is my wife? Where's Gilraen?

I saw what you did there. That was fantastic! I mean, the fire coated your fingers and then you went swoosh! And the fire flew like an arrow and the tubes lit up and the device came to life! I can't wait to try that!

Doesn't it kind of make sense that a foreigner might have broken the Pact? He tried to do right by it as far as I know, but isn't it hard to hold to something unless you've done so all your life?nnAnyway, thanks to you that's settled. Fancy a trade?
That's surprising. I thought he might be involved, but I didn't actually think he was responsible. Poor creature. Someone must have put him up to it.
Lyris wishes to say her goodbyes as well.
We really shook the pillars of Oblivion, didn't we? I'm going to miss you.
I have already said my piece. I have no more words for you. Leave me to my grief.
Don't dawdle. The Daedra could be on us at any moment.
With Aranak gone things won't be the same. We didn't see many traders before him and if word of this gets out I doubt we'll have more.nnIt's all just  awful. Poor Khajiit.
Yes, you have found Adusa. Now go away and let me get back to what I was doing.
Whatever the constable does to me, it'll be better than being eaten by a snake.  At least  at least I hope so.

Oh, yes, of course the Khajiit destroyed the plant. He's been working for them for ages, smuggling in magical powders through his cart and mixing them into our drinks. That's why I only drink water I've distilled myself.
Fancy that. The foreigner violated a crucial tenet of a culture not his own.nnLike that never happens.

You have my gratitude, friend. Let us both remember what happened to these mages. Ambition can carry you to great heights, but when not tempered with patience and wisdom one will often find themselves plummeting to certain doom.
<<1>> kept careful records of her struggle to pierce <<2>>'s seal. They remain scattered in her tower.nnFind them. Use them to breach the seal and recover <<3>>.
Well? You should collect <<Az:1>>, yes?
Can't you feel it? The power? It's calling tonnNo! Adusa must be strong! We must destroy this relic!
We don't have time for any more of your inane questions. We need to get moving.

The vampire commander is in the house on top of the hill. As soon as you get up there and start causing a distraction, Adusa will use stealthy-stealth to escape with these townsfolk.nnMeet us outside of town when the deed is done.

I'm sorry. Did you want to talk about history? Intriguing subject, isn't it?nnI've been in the castle library for days. Fascinating how accounts differ relating to the Siege of Orsinium. The second one, that is.
Thanks for "peace." Malacath would have it end differently.nnJust in case, I'll be keeping my axes sharp.
Did you find anything? Was I wrong about the flowerswere they still there?
Heard Gargak's still alive, something about a mine. Don't care. Still feels like there's a snake in my guts.nnI ever meet him, just him and me, I'll show him how much I like that.
Yeah, I heard. Gargak's not dead, that's great. You did good.nnSomeone should filthy his well, show him what it's like.
I'll find a sparring partner from Gargak's bunch. Without poison, there won't be a match for me.
gargak not dead
gargak not dead
gargak not dead
gargak not dead
gargak not dead

I can't believe it. He was right again. When will I learn not to wager my gold against Razum-dar's instincts?nnHe said you would be coming this way. Is it true then? Did you persuade the Wilderking to swear loyalty to Queen Ayrenn?
I don't care about the past. More ore to armor our camp? That's good.nnSpeaking of girding, nobody works plate like me. Browse if you like.
It is good you are here. Your talents are needed.
I'm helping Shakul arm the stronghold. We have an early start, if you'd like to trade!
Let me get this straight. Gargak's built another stronghold just across the way, with its own mine? Wonder if he needs a good brewer .
Gargak's still squatting in that old Imperial tower? Can't be good for trade.nnUnless you come to us. Trade?
Less dead is less dead. More mouths to feed, which is fine by me.nnHungry? I can help with that.

It is bad luck to owe a life debt to a stranger, so I have decided that you are my friend. Know that my people do not take such things lightly. If by life or death I can serve you, I will do so without hesitation.
He tried to order me to return to the camp.nnFoolish man. As if I'd leave him now!
This one hates this place. It feels  evil.
You! Come to gloat at my torment? Or is your appearance here a part of it?
The lever's on the wall right over there. nnYou're a real life-saver. Can't tell you how glad I am you happened along.
I admit that I didn't trust the Khajiit at first, but she's certainly helped us a lot today. I guess you really can't judge a book by its cover.
You're really going out there? To confront the vampire commander? You're so brave!
Quickly, throw the Prismatic Weapon into the Mortuum Vivicus!
If you're going to the village, get going.
Where am I? It was like I fell asleep, but then there was this terrible pain .nnI remember you. You're the one who helped my husband. Oh, Renoit! Are you all right? Did I hurt you?
I must have a device or construct somewhere in here.nnDon't mind us. We'll hold this area. Somehow.
Do whatever you need to do. My brother and I will make sure nothing gets through here.nnWe might even be able to test some of Raynor's newest prototypes. That's always good for a laugh!
Well, that was short-lived. Go on, I'll get this bandaged up and get back to the portal. You don't have time to wait around for me.
I always wanted to see a planar vortex up close and personal. Isn't that sky spectacular?nnWait, what are we doing here again?
Timing is everything. When will the gifts be opened, I wonder?

This is absurd! I have committed no crime, and they are just going to leave me here  I would say to rot, but I will never get that chance.nnI'll be speared through when the city is taken, and then these damned crows will eat my remains!
Do not concern yourself with me. My wounds are only superficial. nnThere are many here in greater need of assistance than myself.
Find them, as quickly as you can. I know you can do it.
Like I said, talk to the crow. It knows more than I do, that's for sure.
When there's no knowledge in the tops of towers, check the bottoms of bottles.
Are you really going out there? To confront the vampire commander? You're so brave!
It's always an honor to have you in our village. Please, make yourself at home for as long as you like.
Friends, foes, and fools  hard to know which is which  or who is who. Choose poorly and wind up dead.
If you're looking for the Captain, you can find her in the camp. Countess Eselde says our primary duty is to always help the common folk, and that's just what we're doing here.
Come to join the battle?
The deed is done. My sister died with dignity and honor, still in the holy light of blessed Arkay.nnWe can grieve later. Right now, we still have a war to win.
<<1>> can tell you more. I need to watch the road, warn away travelers.
You should know <<1>> has some sort of position in <<2>>. Seems to think her reputation precedes her. No need to kiss the hem of her robes, but she's far less prickly if you show her some respect.
I'll be fine. There's still a chance to stop this.nnAnd after all "<<1>>" has done, you shouldn't feel the need to hold back.
It's not time yet! The mayor said you can't eat me until dinner!

Choice wins again. Really tugs at the heart-strings! Careful with those. Yank too hard, and the blood goes everywhere but up.nnI really do admire this town. Shame I can't take it with me. Oh, but can't I? I know just where to put it!
Ready to move on, hero? Verandis sent word to me. I know where we need to go next.
Forgive a foolish old man his ramblings, Vestige. We've no time for fears or regrets, our path is clear.nnSai Sahan awaits. Go speak with him.
Mannimarco. Bah! I do not like necromancers. They are ruthless, blasphemous, and egotistical. And those are Mannimarco's best qualities.
I'm worried about Sai. First the Halls of Torment, then the destruction of the Valley of Blades? A lesser man would have already crumbled.
Do you understand what you've done? Without <<1>> in <<Az:2>>, we're stuck here!
What more is there to discuss, comrade? Kill all the Black Daggers you find!
The Black Dagger bandits bring terror and death to the folk of Cyrodiil. You must help us end this.
I wish I could hunt down Black Daggers with you and the other guild members. But I'm stuck in here, handing out contracts. Go kill a few for me.
Despite his  abrasive personality, Tharn could be a useful ally. Sometimes the best way to find out whether you can trust someone is simply to trust them.
It would appear I have little choice in what's to come.
I guess I should thank you for getting me to a safe location. This is a safe location, isn't it? I need to lie down for a bit.
I just need a minute to catch my breath.
You've brought Lyris back! And largely intact, from the look of her.
The Khajiit wants us to leave? Abandon Moira's Hope? I'm not sure how I feel about that.
Go back to the Harborage. Get the ring to safety!
You should leave for the Harborage immediately! More Worm Cultists are most assuredly on their way here!
Our orders were to protect the Mages Guild in their excavation, so you'll have to see to your own defense. We're spread too thin to do anything but guard this camp.
Tragic. He did nothing to deserve such an end. He was the model husband.nnAlmost.
The priestess will set you after the relics we lost. I know it.
The priestess will set you straight. Mara's blessings be upon you.
Sai Sahan is alive? Thank the gods! He's a tough old boulder, but even a rock will crack if you strike it in the right place.

I hope you'll forgive me for making assumptions, but  well, you look like someone who knows how to fight. I mean, if not, then you certainly fooled me. nnIf you do know how to fight, well then, we could really use your help.
We will rescue Sai Sahan as soon as Tharn's preparations are complete, you have my word.
My poor husband. I miss him so much. But I still have family. We'll put this nightmare behind us. Somehow.
That structure up ahead is your destination. It was designed to be a mockery of one of the greatest architectural pieces of the age.nnYou'll find the Mad Architect there.
This region isn't safe for casual travel, my friend. I have been scouting the area for House Tamrith, and <<1>>'s blood-leeching minions swarm across the land like stink-flies drawn to rotting meat.
What a disaster! The blasted creatures came out of nowhere. It happened so fast.nnIf you're here to help, speak to Countess Tamrith. She's moving around the camp, tending to the wounded.
One portal to the gates of Evermore right here for you. nnGood luck. From what I've heard, you're going to need it.
I don't know if you picked the best time to visit Evermore, but if you know how to use that weapon, I expect you will be treated as an honored guest.nnPlease excuse me, thoughI must see to my duties.

I was able to grab some of my wares as we fled the horrors in Crestshade. A good merchant must always be ready to help his customers buy and sell, you understand.nnAnd I am nothing if not a good merchant.
I've been salvaging a few things here and there. In times like these, you never know what might come in handy!
Squire Theo says Etienne is dead, and this Medya Zurric is the villain responsible.nnIt is good she is apprehended. Justice will be seen to.
We should just kill her. It'd save everyone the trouble, and we know she's at fault.nnEtienne is dead! She deserves death for that!

I've heard about what happened. It's a shame about what happened to Sir Etienne.nnI'm not certain most would have chosen to spare Medya, considering the circumstances. I'm glad you did, even if she was bad.
That Zurric woman let Sir Etienne die and she's still alive?nnWhat is Theo thinking? What are you thinking?

Can't say I saw any of this coming. I was sure that sweet old woman was just an apothecary, or something.nnThough come to think of it, I did think it was strange her house was on the other side of all the reachmen.
Give me one good reason I shouldn't march over there and take her head off.nnGo on, I'll wait.
Let me be clear with you: I don't care whether Medya Zurric lives or dies.nnI'm not carrying her. I don't carry witches. She walks. That's all.
I never would've believed Medya Zurric was behind any of this, but there it is.nnThis is just horrible. Everything is horrible.
They told us her son was a witchman! And she's still alive, right there? What if another creature comes out of her to kill us all?nnIt could happen, I swear it could!
I see you're still alive. I guess that's something.
Watch yourself. Wouldn't want these dead men making off with all the loot.
Watch your back. These dead men are hungry.
I have the ship's security well in hand. You'd do best to deal with the dead on these docks.
I'll protect the ship and Captain Marck. None of these dead men are getting past me.nnGet out there and deal with it. Do what you do best.
No dead man is taking our boat. No dead man is getting near Lambur, either.nnYou deal with those docks. We'll deal with things here.
It's like Betnikh all over again, isn't it? Like Carzog's Demise. At least this time, they aren't eating our souls.
Someone needs to deal with whatever's happened on these docks, and you're the one I'd trust to do it. Get out there.nnWe'll be fine. I'll have bandages ready in case anyone is wounded.
Worry not for us, my friend. This ship will not fall while we guard it.
Find anything interesting rooting around in my clothing?nnYou'd best leave.
Was that Queen Arzhela I saw storming into the throne room? She used to come in like that on King Eamond when he was  acting up.nnMaybe she's feeling like herself again.
Blessings of Tava be upon you. The magistrate of Bergama sent me hence to explore trade opportunities. nnAlas, it seems the people of Evermore have nothing to trade but trouble.
Did you see those witches back there? I followed one here from Hallin's Stand. She tricked methe dungheap wench! She stole one of the books from the Mages Guild!
No wonder the townsfolk are so glum. Look at this throne room. I've seen more cheer in a mausoleum.
So Queen Arzhela's back in the castle? Something bad has happened, hasn't it?nnI thought I could sense trouble in the air even yesterday.
Oh, my beloved queen  if you see her, please tell her she must eat. nnSince the king's death, she just isn't taking care of herself.
My estate lies in ashes and the queen does nothing! Thank the Eight that Duke Renchant rules in her stead.
I'll bring <<1>> to <<2>>. I don't know if she'll be happy there, but perhaps the Elden Tree will remind her of Falinesti.nnAre you ready to hand over <<3>>? I promise to keep it safe.
I didn't burn down that house! I swears on all ten of my toes!
Stibbons is  Stibbons is a Goblin! Whatever am I going to do with a Goblin manservant?
This is it! Cast the heart into the circle!
Come back and visit anytime. Just don't tell Freyda that I suggested it .
There may be fewer trolls if you stay out of the dig site. There is a natural path down at the northwestern lip that should take you down near the cave entrance.
Duke Renchant appears to be trying his best. Alas, his best is woefully inadequate.
There is no way I'm going back outside. These fools don't believe me, but I swear on Julianos' little teapot I saw a man get torn to pieces by a flock of crows not ten feet from me. It was horrific!
These foolish, dungy Bretons starve while a banquet flies overhead! Famine? Ha! Anisha eats like a queen! Crow is bony, yes, but tasty!
Curse these crows and their incessant cawing! By Arkay's beard, I thought gulls were bad.

I won't lie to you, friend. Things are grim. The king and his heirs are dead, our forces decimated. Crows are everywhere. People have lost hope. nnBring Strastnoc's head to Captain Hjurrun at the south gate. That'll be a big win for us.
Honor to you and your house, sera. Have you come seeking membership in the Fighters Guild?
We have an impressive assemblage of weaponry, is it not so? nnMembership in the guild has a great many benefits. You should speak with Steward Vedra.
Greetings. You look like you've got a strong arm. Any interest in signing on with the guild? nnYou should speak with Steward Vedra if you've a mind to join up.
Salt and stone, look at this. You swagger well enough, but how good are you with a weapon? If you fight as good as you swagger, you should join up with the Guild.
A wolf tried to eat me once, you know. Just because we're in the nature realm, you think we can be friends now?nnMaybe. Did that Hagraven trap your spirit here as well?
Ah, so many musty old tomes to sort and catalog. Some might call this thankless work. Me? I call it paradise.

Hail! Welcome to the Evermore chapter of the prestigious Mages Guild! nnI can tell by your eyes you're an avid reader. You've got the mage's squint to be sure. Don't suppose you've got any interest in joining? We're all about the books, you know.
I can tell you this muchwith all due respect for the royal guardQueen Arzhela could not be any safer than she will be under my protection.nnI look out for the ladies, you know  queens included.
Whenever you're ready to go to the parley site, let me know and I'll open a portal.nnLet's hope that creating portals is the only magic we need today.
Blessings of Julianos be upon you, my friend. Take care on the road. Bangkorai has become a dangerous place as of late.
I'm to travel with <<1>> to <<2>>. I wonder how much it has changed.nnDo you know if they still run the boars through its streets? I do miss the running of the boars.
I spent a month trying to convince Kerbol to take me in. Not about to ruin all that work by blabbing off to an outsider.nnIf Kerbol wants you to know something, she'd already have told you.
Most of these crates contain fabric and trade-goods, but no food. nnSoon I'll be asking the provisioner if he has a decent recipe for shoe leather.

I just arrived from Deshaan. I'm with the Maulborn. Perhaps you've heard of us? We help the poor and protect the weak! You know, issues too mundane to concern the Tribunal.nnI'm here to spread the word and warn people about the Llodos plague.
Who knew that joining the Maulborn would involve so much heartache! All these people. They're so  sick.
Our guildhouse is new, but with the queen's blessing and your support we will grow quickly.
Gods, the duke could have spared us a few tents when we arrived. nnIt's bad enough to be forced from our homes. Now we have to live in squalor.

I signed on as a farm hand just days ago. Then the Reachmen arrivedscores of them. One stabbed my friend with a knife made from an antler! nnMark me, I'll return the favor when we're released from this camp.
I would walk on if I were you, stranger. This town is cursed.
Kerbol doesn't like us talking to outsiders. Too much at stake, she says.nnIt's a bit silly, I know. But after all she's done for us, how can I refuse her?
I promised to Kerbol, to the village. Please, ask me nothing. I cannot get involved!
Why don't you leave us alone? We came here to get away from people like you!
There is no time! Kill the Titan!
All are welcome among the Fighters Guild, so long as you have a stout heart and little tolerance for the darkness that has seeped into this world. Are you here to join our cause?
Yes! Happy!
I left the Alik'r seeking aid against the Withered Handbut I see the people of Evermore have their own problems.
It is good that the queen has returnedshe has a warm heart, and cares deeply for her people. nnBut it will take more than good intentions to reclaim our homes.
Hello! Do you have business for the Guild?
Well, you don't look like much, but you're welcome in the Fighters Guild.nnLong as you've got guts and the teeth to take a bite out of Oblivion, that is.
Every day is an adventure when you're part of the Ravenwatch, yes?
I won't forget what you've done for me.
We can't escape her voice. She controls us like puppets.
Your actions today impress me. And believe me, it's not an easy feat.
Mannimarco is an egotistical cretin. The only thing more frustrating than a pompous ass in a position of power are those foolish enough to listen to him.
Yet another hopeful? Don't look like much.nnIt'd be wise of you to wait a few days to compete. I'll have moved on by then. You might actually have a chance!

Come on now, don't stare. Andoriel and Raz may be enjoying themselves, but this whole thing just makes me uncomfortable.nnI have no issue following the treethane's commands; I just hope this is over quickly.
I feel so beautiful and  tall. I could get used to this.

Isabeth was a foolish girl. I should have disciplined her better. Made her stronger. She never followed orders. I knew this way of life would get her killed.nnHow can I possibly consent to this alliance with her blood on their hands?
Thank you for helping us. I'm really the one that should have gone back in, not Isa. Hatmi is my sister. Stendarr watch over them and bring you all back safe.
You're no Reachman. Stendarr's finally seen it fit to grant me a little mercy.
I was on my way back to Evermore when I noticed Northglen's been overrun. Those poor souls. Simple farmers. I can't imagine what the Reach have done to them.
The village dweller didn't make it, did she? I didn't think she would.

Even together, my sisters and these soldiers can only prevent these Reachmen from advancing further south.nnDefeating the Dark Witnesses for good will require that someone goes deeper into their territory to kill the Hagraven, Uela.
If you're going to finish Isabeth's work, be careful. She's very resourceful, for a city dweller. If the Dark Witnesses have her, they could easily grab you as well.
We should return to my fathat is, Captain Gaercroft.
Please. Get that amulet as far away from here as possible. I never want to see it again.
We thought we could protect these people, but we were wrong. The vampires overwhelmed us.nnCountess Tamrith has been trying to gather the survivors. Talk to her when you get a chance.
This creature disturbs the woods with the Sentinel's binding as a token!nnHas the forest not bent to the whims of the Sentinel already? What more can we give?
Well, look who it is! Fancy meeting you here! And you have that look in your eyes. nnYes. I'm betting that like myself, Rivenspire's troubles have become your troubles as well. Am I right?
I'll be watching for the flames. If you pull this off, we'll have to celebrate!
Just kill me, you crazy freak.nnWait, you're not him. You aren't dancing. Who are you?

I shudder to call any arena more civilized, but this notion of matches being to the death  well, it is concerning. I could live without an arm or leg or eye, but I cannot live without my head!nnStill, though, the notion remains tempting.
I thank you for bringing me closure on my son's killer. I know what I have to do now.
I'm sorry, I'm retired.
I fear that Montclair will have a surprise or two waiting for us within the Doomcrag. I suddenly have the feeling that bringing an army up here was a terrible mistake.

I hope it was not a mistake to send the herbalists out to the lake. I knew the knights would need poultices and I wanted to be prepared.nnI would never forgive myself if one of my friends was killed, though.
Hail. If you plan to journey to North Glen, be wary.

Our mission is crucial, guildmate. Never forget that. The war effort in Cyrodiil, the raids on our homes, the issues of the common people - none of it will matter if Molag Bal has his way with this world. We can't let that happen.
So now the new constable's going around confiscating people's things like he owns the entire town?nnI don't understand why the mayor's not doing anything.
I feel sorry for old Agazu. She must have known this day was coming, but the mayor should have at least given her a warning!
If you ask me, Agazu was never cut out to be constable in the first place. She's better at weighing down a barstool.
I've been waiting for weeks for those new amethysts to come down from the mine! nnIf I don't get a new ring, I'm going to be shopping around for a new husband.
It wasn't all of the Bretons? Just a few bad apples, I suppose. I guess I'll have to start being friendly again.
You mean the Orcs didn't rob the Bretons? I guess I better return these things to Hierot then.
Do you think the mayor fired Agazu because she's an Orc? I do. And if that's where this town is headed, I'll be headed to another town.
I knew those Fell's Brigade thugs were up to no good!
I do not understand. Why is everything so quiet? Things are changing in this town, and I am concerned that they are not for the better.nnPerhaps it is time to move on.
Leonce may be the scapegoat, but I still think that all of the Bretons are guilty of something.
That Bailiff Sagabar is such a dunderhead! He takes three rooms for three nights and then he just tells me he didn't need two of them. nnHe gave me back the keys, but he refuses to pay!
<<1>> was such a grimy place. The new mayor is really cleaning things up, don't you agree?
Ah, such a shameful misunderstanding.nnPlease tell this guard you saw the thief that ran through here. You wouldn't want to see an innocent Khajiit spend the night in the stocks!
Surely this scoundrel is lying. I chased him here on my own two legs. He was only out of sight for a flick of the tail!

Shornhelm is no longer a city divided. I'm glad we were able to accomplish that before the High King arrived.nnAnyway, accept my thanks for the help you provided. I tend to forget to perform such niceties, so you may not hear that from me again.
I do apologize, but I can't speak right now. I must prepare the beds for their arrival.
While you were gone, we liberated the upper city. House Montclair's hold on Shornhelm has been shattered.
The fire warms us when we're cold, but burns us when we're close. No matter how much you feed it, its hunger never ends.nnThe fire is sublime.

The remains of the royal family have vacated this place. They return to the land of living to follow the anointed and to avenge their bloodline.nnPrince Adrien is the anointed. He too has been blessed to rise again.
The whole town went crazy! It's just inconceivable, impossible, unbearable!nnIf this is just how things are here, I need to offload my wares so I can go set up shop elsewhere.
Well! I suppose I can't go back to town, now, can I?nnI'll just make myself comfortable here for a while. This sort of thing usually sorts itself out, doesn't it?
I know there's a war afoot and all that, but there's a problem here at the graveyard. nnThe corpses are climbing out of their graves! I promisethis isn't my fault! I buried them all real good!
Speak with <<1>>. If he finds you worthy, we may speak again.
I can't stand all the bickering. Bretons and Orcs, accusing each other of terrible things. It's disgraceful!nnI remember when we were all just citizens of Fell's Run.
This one thought we were troll food!
Go on, my five-clawed friend! Show him the treasures you recovered from the tomb!
Hello. How about a helping hand? Seem to have gotten myself into some trouble.nnNot for the first time.
I need your help!nnThese blithering idiots are talking about selling us off into slavery!
By the Divines, have you come to help? Please tell me you'll free me!

You have seen the past through my eyes. You know that all of this is my fault. My involvement altered the power of the relic. I was forced to kill Leila when she became a bloodfiend.nnAnd now Montclair seeks to end death and claim Ranser's throne.
I've had some valuables go missing, but I can't believe that any of my neighbors had anything to do with it. We're all friends here.
We gave the Imperials a healthy kick in the buttocks, didn't we? I bet they don't stop running until they're behind the walls of Hallin's Stand!nnWe will have to go after them  of course.
As grateful as I am to have Emeric and the Lion Guard here, it's your presence that gives me the most comfort.nnWhere you go, hope follows.
Take pity, yes? Khajiit has not eaten in days! My family, they starve on the roadside! Anything you can spare, please!
You look like someone who knows the value of a smart organization. Let me tell you, our noble triumvirate falls far short of the definition of either smart or organized.
Very hungry. Soup smells nice.
I don't get a lot of business from outsiders and my stock is limited, but take a look.
I thought I recognized you! You were right in the middle of those Imperial bastards. Well done, comrade. Stendarr protect you.
Hey, you're one of those Hollow Moon types! What do ya got for me?
Spare some food for an old coin?
The camp is just south of the abandoned orc settlement.
Thank you for  for your kindness. Once  once I'm strong again, I'll find a way to re  to repay you.

Did the captain give you the poultices? Hang on to them. They heal the user and grant temporary invisibility.nnThere should be enough for you as well once you find all the scouts. It wears off rather quickly, so don't use it until the time is right.
My brother sleeps now, and he is quiet. A welcome reprieve, if fleeting. Soon, the shakes will return.
You my friend are a murderer and I should have you arrested. You have slain my hunger!
You found my Puddles!

I'm not one to turn away a traveler in need of shelter or supply, but a word of friendly advice: do your business and move along.nnTrouble has us in his ropes, and they say the Herd Mother has forsaken us.
I don't need your charity, whelp  but I do appreciate it.
We've done it! We've reached the top of the Doomcrag! Now we can finally learn the secret of the ancient Ayleid relic and save my wife.
Verandis, you mustn't say anything. Please! I'm sure this will  this will pass. I just need the stone. Another treatment and I'll be fine.
We are not the woods' master, nor is it ours. It's a rather complicated arrangement, as are most such dependencies.
We're free!nnI  had I tears to shed I would weep.

Are the nobles still bickering? Or discussing strategy, as they like to say? Gives me a headache.nnI needed to do something, so I decided to look around in here. Seems to be something up ahead, past the angry skeletons.
A team works best together when the members know and trust each other, but I can understand if you're ready to get to work.
Our lives are simple, and our motives pure. There's nothing better than a clear conscience, is there?
Oh divine lord, protector of the eternal balance between life and death, I beseech you  remove this dark curse from your sacred grounds
I hope you do not intend to sojourn south, wayfarer. The situation is even worse there, I assure you
The Mad Architect is gone! We've won!
I didn't want it to end this way .
You've proven wise in your judgement.
Greetings, comrade! You come to me with bloodied claws, yes?
Ugh. Are you as anxious as I am to get out of this place?
Hold a moment. What business have you in Bangkorai Garroh. A thousand pardons, I didn't recognize you. Welcome back, my lady.
We're grateful for your help.
Be quiet, walker! This one listens for sounds of another Imperial raid! Must stay focused!
Have you been to Pelin Graveyard? nnI  I just need a minute. nnActually, I need a drink.
What did you use to ward against the plague again?
Pay attention, walker! Crazy Eye sees more Imperials coming!
Our walls are in bad shape. Any more breaches and we'll be sitting ducks. We can't escape with all these wounded.
No more bandits to fight. Oh, well.nnIt's all right. Was running out of room on my blades for notches.

I'll be honest with you. I didn't think we could retake the garrison. I expected to die here. I was even looking forward to it.nnBut my heart is filled with happiness right now. Not for myself, but for the people of Evermore.
Hello, friend. Do you need directions to the inn?

Good. We will set aside differences for the sake of Tamriel.nnWe need to know what happened here, and surviving members of the group sent to destroy the Dark Anchor will know best. We must split up and search.
Ah, a hatchling in search of wisdom. Are you acquainted with the Mages Guild, my friend? You would do well to join us.
How dare the fools invade Ravenwatch Castle! Did they really think they could prevail against us?
<The suspicious bottle is empty.>
Being out in the air has made me more courageous than usual. Oh, tree nuts! When we find Maugruhl, I'll back you up. nnJust keep in mind. Fighting's not my usual area of expertise.
<<1>> wants to speak with you. I've opened a portal. Step through whenever you're ready.
Montclair's nephew is close. Adusa can smell Rohlbert from here.
Any ore will be back as far we can go. The walls near the entrance are all played out.
We've got to find out what Armando knows.
We've got to find out what Armando knows.
We've got to find out what Armando knows.
She's warming up to me. I can tell.
Did you see that rat? It was huge!
Look, I've just about had it .nnOh! I'm sorry. I thought you were that lecherous bailiff again. He tries to grope me every time I bring him a drink.
Go on now. Give the trinket a try!

You know, I've been drinking at this inn for years, and I always sit in the same chair. Right over there. But that bothersome new bailiff made me leave. nnSaid the table is his and I should just drink over here. What an arse!
I can't say I enjoy this, but knowing <<1>> is trapped inside these walls gives me no small amount of satisfaction.
They're back! And he is in so much trouble! Thank you.
<<1>>! Thank the Divines for you, pup! And you as well, stranger. Did he come and find you? He's such a good boy!
<<<1>> barks excitedly.>
The Doomcrag! It's gone! You had something to do with that, didn't you? Yes, I'm sure of it.nnCan we please go back to Northpoint now? I've had more than enough of this dreadful place.
Do you see this? Reachmen all over Northglen! My family .
What word, my friend? Is Verandis ready for the troops to ascend the Doomcrag?
I rejoice that you still live. Arkay's blessings served you well. Cesabelle has returned. What of the others?
These are all the supplies we have left. If the Imperials want them, they'll have to go through me to get them.
Is there anything I can do for you?

So the bright, young Countess Tamrith is your choice. I know she is thoughtful, humble, and sharp as an assassin's dagger. I am sure she will make a courageous queen.nnQueen Eselde of Shornhelm. It even has a nice ring to it.
So little time, so many dead  I'd wager those corpses up at Flyleaf Catacombs are going to be pretty ripe before I get to them.
My lazy clerk has yet to return and time grows short. I find it increasingly more difficult to find good help in these trying times.
The king won't keep us here forever. For all his flaws, my cousin believes himself to be a just man.nnHe can't leave us here to rot.

Thank you for the vote of confidence, my friend. I promise you, I will do everything in my power to restore Rivenspire to its former glory.nnWe will tell stories of your courage to inspire our soldiers. And you will always be welcome here.
Thank you for your faith in me. I will do all that I can to prove I deserve this honor.nnAnd you. You will always be welcome in Shornhelm.
And so the Infinium becomes mine again. As it always does.nnYou performed well against Graccus.
Ayleid defenses? That doesn't sound good. Well, I'm sure you can handle it. Just give a holler if there's any way I can lend a hand.
I shall need time to unravel the sorcery that controls this orb.
Anything else?
Keep it under your hat, but I've got something coming up over in Dawnmead, in the little town of Pa'alat. If you find yourself there anytime soon, it'd be a pleasure to work with you again.
Aha! My mercenary friend. Seeing you does me good, but the look on <<1>>'s face, aheh. A price beyond measure.
Well done. You fought like a Vinedusk Ranger.nnWith <<1>>'s sons in custody, the Blacksap is dead. Perhaps <<2>> will finally be at peace.
The more I think about it, the more I like this idea of moving to Shornhelm and turning honest. nnJust a few more deals and I might even have the coin. I'll start saving up tomorrow.
Look here! If it isn't Strastnoc's bane!nnHave you come down to lop off a few more Reachmen heads? There are plenty to go around down these parts.
<<<1>> barks excitedly.>
Good choice. Strength and a good army a better than any moderate political view.
Our family is back together. I can never thank you enough.
Ironic. We come back to my homeland and I'm the one that falls into a ravine. I used to scale these rocks like they were stairs.nnI guess none of us are immune to the ravages of time.
Whatever are you doing in this place? I'm somewhat perplexed by your appearance in this backwater.nnStill, it's not as though we can be too picky about our help these days.
Please, break the curse. Go to Hoarfrost before it's too late.
I thank you for bringing the ring back and ending this madness. I know what I have to do.
Sorry, whatever you want, I can't help you. I'm retired.
I thank you for bringing me closure on my son's killer. I know what I have to do now.
My people are lucky to have someone like you standing by the candidates. Well done, Hallowed.
You've done well, Hallowed. I can see the echoes of moonlight hanging in the air. Jone and Jode  they are pleased.
I hope these relics truly help against the undead. Alvaren is confident they will. We shall see.
If you unlock this cage, I'll be your best friend for life.
Make sure to say hello to the grumpy Redguard over there. He may seem cranky, but he's a good man and a better vampire slayer.
If you are done delaying our mission, let the big Nord over there know.
The spider cave is near Camp Tamrith, but I wouldn't want to face the spider queen one-on-one, even if I wasn't a coward with a splitting headache.
I'm never drinking another drop. Just water for me from now on. Well, beer is mostly water. Just water. And beer.
I'm glad this <<1>> business is settled.nnBetween the two of us, I'm tired of all this talk of embassies.
The preparations for this ratification ceremony seem endless. But I'm up to the task.

Join me for a cup of mead. A toast to those we've lost. My parents to death and my sister to her crazy dreams. nnWe're all going to go sometime. We might as well have a drink or two before it happens.
That's far enough. The storeroom is off limits. <<1>>'s orders.
Please, look for Firaelion in the cave to the north. But be careful. I couldn't bear it if something happened to you, too.
I won't forget how you saved me from the spiders. If there's anything I can ever do for you, please don't hesitate to ask.
This will be a day long remembered.
Thank you, outsider.
Do it. And quickly.

Ah, the proven hunter. I see you have the briar heart, torn from the chest of the Reachman. His punishment for failure is to roam the Hunting Grounds as prey. His chest, a gaping hollow, a reminder of his weakness.
There! See, I told you it would work!
This spy business works a lot better if we don't stand around and talk about it all day.
What is going on? Is it true? Has someone sent an assassin after me?
I trust we can rely on you to be discreet about your involvement with us.
Saw you standing over the body of a dead Wood Elf. Nearly put an arrow in your throat.nnGood thing I recognize you.
I have things about as under control in here as they can be.nnYou should go on ahead - if you can do anything about our entrenchment here, please do.nnOur injured soldiers would thank you for it.
My head feels like a thunderbug crawled inside it.nnBut I did win our contest. Oblan will bring the laundry for you. Every morning.

Here we have the savior of Shornhelm, I presume? You should know that Baron Dorell and Countess Tamrith have been quite generous in their praise of you. nnI trust you were able to close this portal Montclair was using to bring in reinforcements?
My father has many friends in <<1>>. They'll see us out of this mess.
Not sure what's more surprisingthat we made it to Shornhelm or that you did. Did you find Marien's necklace?
Oh, hello! Our friend from the road. Nothing like good honest work to make you feel alive, am I right?
This Darien  I perhaps mistook him when we first met.nnHe is a caring man. Still a man who thinks not always with his head. But he has honor at least.

The shard holder, whoever it is, uses the power of the remnant to veil himself. Just like Lleraya did back in Northpoint. There's no way you're going to find him by yourself.nnThis is a trap that we have to step into.
By the look of things, you're probably one of the ones fighting the Reachmen. That's good.nnWe don't have dissimilar goals, but remember: That doesn't make us friends.
Hey! I'd recognize that bow anywhere. Where did you get that?
<<1>> said the entrance to the vampire's lord lair is in the valley north of town. We need to get there immediately.
Just place my family's ashes in each of the graves. Then I'll say a few words to send them on their way.
It's a great comfort to have you participate in this solemn occassion. I think my little brother would have liked you. A lot.
All that we can do, all that we can become, now that we are free, is halting. We do not know where to begin.

Look for a ship called the Dawn Posset offshore at Northpoint. The first mate, Elvira Derre, should be waiting for you on the docks, ready to leave for Sentinel.nnWhen you get there, just make sure the city is safe. Only visit my father if you wish.
Ah, good. You've returned. Sai Sahan has recovered, and there is much to be done.
The people of <<1>> will know what we've done for the Green Pact. The king won't have any recourse but to pardon us all.nnYou've done more for the Blacksap Rebellion than you'll ever know.
I need to look into a few lingering issues of my own here. I'll be along as soon as my brother tells me everything's ready.
Why do I think this isn't going to end wellfor me?
I've been thinking of Nedras a lot recently. I keep thinking I'll see him come through my door, hear his voice. But never again.
