Ah, you return! And I can sense the Ayleid energy you carry, so I don't even need to ask whether you were successful. I hope you caused plenty of trouble for the Worm Cultists.

It's decided, then. I'm going to take up weaponsmithing. My father was always very handy with an anvil. Perhaps I'll try to earn an apprenticeship  sorry, please excuse me. I have a lot of planning to do!
Kala must consider how she will find the coin for travel. That brother of mine  never thinking of anything but the moons!

It's a disgrace. I fought by <<1>>'s side in the civil war. Things got so bad, we had to eat leather cut from our own armor.nnEven then, I never heard this amount of whining coming from the High Elves and the Khajiit about their embassy.
Completely unacceptable! If this is what <<1>> thinks of us, we should go back to Elsweyr!

Yours is truly a generous spirit to release me from this dark place, but I would be most ungrateful if I did not tell you the entire truth.nnIf I am truly to leave hereto put down new roots and find new lifemore is needed to be done.

Dark moons, stranger. While Silver-Paws and dungy Knight-Commander quibble over bow strings and bandages, food stockpiles shrink. nnWe must start hunting now, or we will all be dead before the next Tojay moon.
If you ask me, the Baron was too easy on his son. People died. On his watch. Blatant incompetence at its finest.
With so many knights injured here, there's great demand for fighters willing to take their places. Why not join the guild?
Grim scene out there, eh? Almost makes me feel bad for not helping out. nnBut hey, adversity builds character, right? Knights like to have character, I hear.
I am new to the Guild, but I think it's the life for me. Paid to fight! Sounds good to me.
My hunting companion was chased by a group of chanting cultists up near the <<1>>. What's this world coming to? I certainly can't make any sense of it.
These knights are fools if they think force of arms alone will retake the Garrison. Without magical assistance they'll be slaughtered.
Do you have a thirst for adventure, for knowledge, for the arcane? You've come to the right place. Join us!
Do not tarry here with the wounded. You must  you must retake the Garrison! Don't let our deaths be in vain.
She's going to kill me. In my sleep. I know she will.
Even now, some of my brother and sister knights call for another assault on the Garrison. But we can't even keep light skirmishers out of our camp. Attacking without reinforcement would be suicide.
Do you have a kill for me, pup? Did you bring me meat?
Thank you for assisting Lady Laurent while I was indisposed. nnI hope there are no lingering after-effects. She can be  rather demanding at times.
Daedra take these Imperials. By St. Pelin's blood, I'll see that fort retaken!
I envy my brothers' and sisters' optimism. In its current state, the Order of Saint Pelin could not mount a defense in depth, let alone take back a fortified garrison.

That was an experience I won't be forgetting anytime soon. I'd say that you went beyond the call of duty, but I think you went even beyond that.nnOf course, Septima was actually after you, wasn't she?
These cursed Baandari charge us a king's ransom for supplies, then refuse to assist us in reclaiming them? A pox on the lot of them.
Zeht's tears! What has befallen? Who has slain everyone? Where's the king?
Any luck? Did you find the source of the invaders?
I must thank you for the opportunity to see <<c:1>> operate as it did in ancient times. It's all so exciting!
The queen  she's radiant!
My notes? I can't believe it! I thought I'd lost these for good.
Quite impressive, stopping this attack on <<1>>. I'd say it's worthy of our king's notice.nn<<2>> is always pleased to meet extraordinary people who arrive in his lands.
You don't look like much. Why would Hircine send you to me as a challenger? Does he mock me? Or is there more to you than meets the eye?
Adeena may forgive me in time, but I will never forgive myself.
So. You killed it.
I wish I had heeded my sister's warnings rather than marry such a monster.
A nightmare from Oblivion visited upon our home. May the Roar of Alkosh burn these invaders away!
What do you think you're doing on my ship? Do you know what I did to the last stowaway I found?
Follow the pull of your blood and you will find the Tomb of the Blood Matron.
May the Father of Owls guide your steps, friend.
Not a lot of people simply walk in and volunteer to help fight with the resistance. Call me a skeptic, I suppose.
Watch your step in there. After all, you don't want to wind up stumbling into the afterlife  the gods don't like that.
I'm glad to be free of that monster's flesh, but I can't rest easy until I've passed from this plane.nnI died so long agoI would give anything to move on.
You have no idea what it feels like to have a Khajiit scratching around inside your head.
You did not see me, did you? No one sees the poor, the sick. The oppressed!nnYou help these people of Hallin's Stand, but for what? You put yourself in harm's way, but why?
I thought that brute was going to kill me! Thank you, stranger!
Away with you! Can't you see I'm busy?
What  who  how  oh, hello there.
So it's just us mortals from here on in? That's fine with me. I don't mind admitting that the idea of friendly vampires kind of creeps me out.
The Blacksap always knew the best hunting spots

I sense great determination in you, living one, but very few of the living are foolish enough to trespass in these hallowed halls. nnEven fewer are foolish enough to seek entrance into the Chamber of Passage. This is your intention though, is it not?
Blacksap, Dominion? Who are we following now?
My husband would have been heartbroken if I spoke out against the Blacksap. I'm glad they're gone. Now we can all get back to our lives.
What will Cormount become without the Blacksap? There's no future for any of us.
The Blacksap are no more. What a pity.
Our people are doomed. The High Elves will stomp us out.
I know you, sister. You're one of us, even if you don't know it yet. Hircine calls you. His song is in your blood.

It takes a brave soldier to enter the Chamber of Passage, but courage alone is not what defines a warrior. nnOne has already breached the chamber without my blessing, but you come behind seeking just that, do you not?
This is an historic moment. You do realize that, don't you? nnWe're about to play a significant role in ending the haunting of Traitor's Tor and discovering the truth of King Ranser's final moments!
Finally, a chance for everyone to relax. Join us, if you like.
I appreciated your intervention earlier, but I am sure this conquest can be made without your help.
My beautiful abomination, how you shine in the dark. nnNow listen. I must warn you.
Go upstairs and get the inn key from Darien. Then we can find out what's locked in there and making all that racket.
Brackenleaf's Briars built this shrine, as tribute to the animals of <<1>>.

I sense you have been among that dark ruin, Gil-Var-Delle. Perhaps it was even you who fought back against the vile Worms. If that is true, you must have seen the scarring the land has suffered in that foul place. Maybe you can help me.
The Queen expects you presently. Proceed.
Go on, up the stairs with you. There's no reason to keep the beautiful Lady Lleraya waiting.
My performers can best explain their setbacks. <<1>> is our bug trainer, <<2>> our storyteller, and <<3>> is  well, she's magnificent.nnI have to describe her that way. It's in her contract.
Arkay protect you, my child.

The scrolls speak of the principles of Wisdom, Discipline, Sacrifice, and Devotion, and the seasons of life in which I mastered these principles.nnPlace them in the proper order in which they were mastered.
I wish I'd known she was in here all this time. The more the merrier, I always say.
Filthy, unclawed Bretons! How hard is it to watch over barrels and crates?
The customs clerk in <<1>> should be able to help you locate my shipment. The client is  not a patient woman, so do hurry.

I must say, Darien certainly has a way with the ladies. That's not how I'd go about extracting information from the enemy, but I can't fault his results.nnThe old smuggler's tunnel should lead into the cityif we can get through it.
Moons' blessings, walker. Have you come to help this one save the camp from unclawed Imperials?
Oh, you again. What do you need?
I hope you didn't travel from far away just to see <<1>>. I am not performing at present.nnMy magic cannot function safely in front of a crowd. The, uh, stars are out of alignment.
Blasted cat-folk. They dine on sweet rolls while we choke down spoiled porridge. nnCan't you hear them? Those hissy laughs of theirs . It makes me sick. St. Pelin give me temperance.
Forgive me, but I must tend to my flock. <<1>> should be able to answer any questions you have about her carnival.
You reek of kwama juices  why don't you come inside and spend some time with your granny Alyxe? nnI'll have a hearty chunky brain stew ready soon, or do you like it spongey and raw?
I promised to keep my husband in line, and that's just what I'm going to do. If he even goes near something that smells like criminal activity, he'll answer to the business end of my broom!
What do you have there? A book?
It's good to see Baron Alard again. He is like a brother to me. It's been weeks since we last saw each other.nnI only wish this reunion was under better circumstances.
You have a point, my friendperhaps we're all in this together.nnSeems it's the only way we'll get out of this war alive. Uptight as these High Elves are, they did save our skins.

You and that Wood Elf can lie to yourselves, but the Altmer have a place above all others. It's not a judgmentsimply a matter of fact. Our knowledge and contributions to history ensure this.nnThat Wood Elf needs to learn his place.
We're the only survivors? I will always remember how you saved me, my father, and my betrothed.
I have more than a few copies, so keep the book as long as you wish. A shame none of them are the translated versions!
I have begun to wonder whether all scholars are as troublesome as this one.
Have you got everything you need?

I'm not sure I can ever forget what happened to my brothers because of what you did, but  you saved Kaleen. You saved Shornhelm, too. I can't discount that.nnI guess we'll just have to learn to live with each other.
I can't believe this could possibly be taking you so long. How hard could it be?
Ha! You made it! I never doubted for a moment. I mean, sure, when the top of the entire mountain disappears, you don't expect many people to walk away from that. But here you are!

You looking for a mace, or maybe a bow? You know, for hunting, not, like, fighting.nnJust between you and me, these Imperial skeevers hanging around is killing my business. Nobody wants to be seen arming themselves.
I do not have much to sell, wayfarer. These red-clad brigands took most of my goods as spoils of war. But you are welcome to look over what is left.
Can't talk much. Imperials are always watching. Take my advicebuy some of my expertly crafted armor, then get out of Hallin's Stand altogether.
I can't talk much. Imperials are always watching. Take my advicebuy some of my expertly crafted armor, then get out of Hallin's Stand altogether.
Next time, let's go shopping. Wouldn't that be more fun?
Fancy a good scrap, like I do? You should join the Guild! Go talk to Hlurashe'll help you out.
Bah. So sick of seeing these Imperial bastards strut past the door like they own the place. If someone doesn't start a riot soon, I may have to do it myself.
By the Three, if you slay Daedra half as well as you slay slack-jawed Imperial conscripts you've got a bright future in the Fighters Guild, f'lah.
I won't ask.

I said, go away! Oh  I beg your pardon. I thought you were one of those oafish Imperials looking for another charm potion. As if such a thing would fool a proud daughter of Hammerfell.nnHave you come seeking potions? I offer the best in the city.
You return. Did you have any luck finding the remaining fragments?
Wonderful day for a bloodfiend attack. What can I do for you, citizen?

Thirsty? Ruptga knows those cursed Imperials are. They've nearly drunk me out of a job. Sometimes they even pay. Dogs and sons of dogs, all of them.nnI've managed to hide away some of my better stock, though. Interested?
I didn't do it, whatever it was.
You  are kind to make such an offer, my friend. I actually hurt my sword arm slaying my captors. I could use an ally.nnIf this lot has harmed Esmaeel, I'll bring this cave down around their heads.
Get her out. I'll be right behind you.
Shut the door quickly behind you. The sand gets into everything, especially the alchemical equipment.nnHave you come seeking membership in the Guild?
I knew you'd be back. I also know Naruk is dead. Thank you. Yet again, you've stopped a threat to the city and the Covenant.
This occupation won't last. We Redguards won't labor under an Imperial yokeit's not in our nature. nnTo be honest, I'm surprised the peace has held this long.
I'd stay off the street if I were you. I've seen ill omens in my scrying mirror. nnBlood is going to be spilled here in Hallin's Stand. Very soon.
<Esmaeel lies dead.>
People here just don't understand Khajiit. This one came here to try to build a better life, but now Malira just wants to go back to Khenarthi.

Thanks for putting that cat in her place. Those people can be so stubborn.nnThe Khajiit need to understand that some of their cultural rituals are taboo to the rest of the Dominion. Those of us who are civilized, anyway.

Welcome to The Drowsy Owl, my friend. I would offer you a bed, but the Imperials have soiled them all. What once smelled of jasmine and rose blossoms now smells of boiled meat and dog. Their stench persists despite our efforts.nnMy deepest apologies.
You shouldn't linger, wayfarer. Hallin's Stand is nothing but an Imperial kennel now. I'm bound for the Alik'r as soon as I get the opportunityyou would do well to follow suit.
The shards of my soul are still trapped. Please find them.
You did it. It's so good to see their faces again.
<The Scouting board has a place for me to post my report.>

So when I saw you go down for a nap, I decided this partnership was over. I certainly didn't think you were doing your part.nnThen the mage suddenly stands up and says he's ready to go, and that I have you to thank for it. Is that true?
Just make sure <<1>> is safe. This one is at her wit's end.
Hail, O wayfarer. I beg you, forgive Khada if she has given you cause for offense. She has a temper, and this Imperial occupation has put a strain on all of us.
Hold. You are no servant of the Empire, are you? nnI beg you to forgive my caution, O wayfarer. The red devils have been watching us for days. I fear they will pounce upon us at any moment.
Ah, good, you are not a Daedra. They are this one's enemies, and must not hear this one's plan to escape the vampire skeevers.

An Ayleid artifact, supposedly touched by the gods, will proclaim my sister worthy of becoming the empress of Tamriel.nnBut this changes little. There are those who will always question her right to rule.
I'm  myself. Aren't I?
<<1>> shall lead us to glory. Of that, there can be no doubt.
<There's a new notice on the Warfront board.>
<No new bounty missions have been posted.>
<There's a new notice posted to the Battle board.>
Welcome to the Steeping Sun tea house, wayfarer. Please, sit and abide a while. Breathe deep and ease the shoulders.
<The Scouting board has a place for me to post my report.>
<The Warfront board has a place for me to post my report.>
<No new bounty missions have been posted.>
<There's a new notice posted to the Battle board.>
<The Scouting board has a place for me to post my report.>
<The Warfront board has a place for me to post my report.>
<No new bounty missions have been posted.>
<There's a new notice posted to the Battle board.>

I don't have time for those who have no desire to cleanse Tamriel of the filth infesting it from Oblivion.nnAnd the whole 'undead' thing. It is both relatively new and entirely undesired.nnUnless you've a desire to join the Guild, that is..?
Ugly business out of the streets, eh? Town's been flip-flopping between Eamond and Fahara'jad for so long. This is what happens when you don't pick a side.
We're going back to Reaper's March? Ziss! We were just there a month ago! We're going to go broke, I just know it.
Keep your voice down. You never know who might be listening.
This Khajiit is lucky you stayed my hand. When I'm blind with rage like I was, I have a tendency to start swinging my axe.
Pleasetalk some sense into that Wood Elf. I don't know anything about the Green Pact that he's talking about.nnI've been eating flowers my whole life. They're delectable!
The proud Captain Helenus stands atop the walls by the Craglorn Gates. She is no doubt considering her next move after taking our tower. nnOur tower!
My soldiers have been returning one at a time. Some still complain of numbness. Some are half-blind. But they're alive
Imperial s'wits. Look what they've done to this beautiful city. It's quiet as death. I can barely hear the goats bleating.
I don't know what's worse: the Imperials strutting around beating people to death, or this vile mead. nnI'm inclined to think the latter.
Look who's keeping everyone waiting now.
I've seen enough desert to last a lifetime. Can't wait to get back to the woods, with or without <<1>>.
Thank you. I've asked a lot of you, but it means so much to these refugees.
His honor remains.nnLeave me. Go.
I've just been informed of what's happened at Bangkorai Garrison. It seems my timing is impeccable as ever.nnSo you're the one who's been helping my cousin Arzhela hold the kingdom together?
Without the danger of losing one's life, how can one know life's true value?nnA man must ask himself such things. Contemplation hones the mind as a whetstone hones the blade.
If they hadn't taken us by surprise, I'd have sliced a few of those Imperial dogs to ribbons myself!
You spoke to <<1>>. Did he tell you our plight? Did he tell you all we've lost?
We can't leave Bangkorai until I get my pendant back. Why doesn't my father care about it? Why? I can't believe this has happened to us.
My daughter won't even speak to me. Watch this. <<1>>! <<1>>!nnShe's never forgiven me for our problems. Well, I've trouble of my own.
The passing of <<1>> was a sign from Mauloch. This cursed tower holds nothing for us now.
Run along now, little scamp. This is the grown-up table.
I know what you're thinking. Why would a dignified woman like me keep company with lowlifes such as these?nnBuy me a drink, and maybe I'll tell you.

Sick and tired of being treated like kitten-headed fools by the Thalmor. They file and deliver their papers, sign us empty promises, and what do we have to show for it?nnNothing. Abuse, yes? That is what this is.

So many fellow walkers are upset, disquieted by the silence of the Thalmor when we entreat them for answers.nnThis one knows the burden that is documentation. They were prompt with Vabashi's trade permits. She will be patient with them.
Nerien'eth will hear from me before I leave this plane, and he won't like what I have to say.nnI have an incendiary vernacular.

I should have seen him comingNerien'eth, I mean. I don't care what spells the Daedra gave hima blade between his eyes nnI should have stopped him when I could. But I'm glad you did, for all our sakes.
Nerien'eth's fire wasn't so bad, after a time.nnMy anger burned brighter.
I have been watching out for you. nnIt must be quite an honor to have the high king awaiting your arrival. King Emeric thought you would be here ahead of him, but he has waited for you nonetheless.
Thank you, kind soul. Thank you for sparing my life.
No, no! Why would you kill Buttons? He just wanted to be your friend!

Ah! King Emeric said you might be coming. The Imperials are here. Did you know this?nnThe king and his men are preparing for an attack even now, though they are greatly outnumbered. I think it is good that you are here.
How did you get up here? Did you actually go through all those portals?nnThat must have been a huge pain-in-the-buttocks! Seriously  I can't believe you did that. What's the matter with you?
<This appears to be the dead body of Sir Dubroc, the leader of the expedition sent to Jackdaw Cove by the Knights of Saint Pelin.>
I've had it. <<1>>? She can sit in the fields and rot for all I care. <<2>> may be able to deal with all this work. Semusa cannot!
We received the word about Sir Dubroc. That was a grisly end for a good soldier.
Please, my family is in desperate need of help!
Thank the gods someone has come. The Imperials, they're up to something strange in the ruins ahead.

Be wary. The Knights of Saint Pelin do what we can to keep these lands secure, but recent events have made this a very dangerous place for travelers.nnI have scouts all over Bangkorai but many have failed to report in.
I think I've run out of tears at this point. How could the gods allow this to happen?
Not Emeric. Anyone but Emeric. Please. Please Tu'whacca, have mercy!
This has to be a joke! I travel all the way across the continent, twist my mind in knots over this password, and all that's in here is Willam's old shaving blade?
Nothing down here's in the right place! You know what that means? nnIt just means more dumb-dung I got to deal with before I can get out of here.

Best of luck to you. <<1>>'s sealed up tight, and by Azura's own hand. It'll take some doing to get in, nevermind thwart Molag Bal, rescue <<2>>, and make your way back here.nnSay hello to <<3>> if she's still kicking, will you? It's been an age.
Some would think you're crazy to walk into caves filled with dreugh and goblins. Me, I think you're either very brave, very stupidor, most rarelyyou're very good at what you do.nnWhich is it?

What are you looking at? Did I say you could look at me? I don't think so!nnI don't even want you sharing my air. You're a festering boil on the lip of reality! I don't like boils or things that fester! Move on  or do you have a problem with that?
Don't! Please! You're going to eviscerate me, I just know it! I don't want to be eviscerated! It sounds awful!
I thought I was dead. Pieces of my life: family, friends  adventures, regrets. I could see it all. nnI can't even begin to tell you how thankful I am you got me out of there.
Whatever it isdon't.
The Lady says you are one of the Undaunted. Welcome. Newcomers buy drinks.
Leave me be, you wretched, joyful young thing. I am old, with little time left in this life. I would not waste what remains talking with the likes of you.
You again? I see you're still sticking your nose in other people's affairs. Well, if you're here to help, I'm not going to turn you away.
Once we get to Coldharbour, it'll be open season on Daedra!

May Auri-El grant us the wisdom to reconsider our individual desires and concur on a halfway-state that best fits all Dominion peoples here in Elden Root.nnThis is not a time for strength, or certainty, but a measure of social kinship.
I was skeptical about this summit until I heard that you were involved. You've been of invaluable help to me in the past.
Please don't distract me. If I don't finish packing, Lady Laurent will give me quite the talking to.
Security couldn't be tighter. This should go off without a hitch.
It's great to see you again, old friend! I feel better knowing that you're part of this invasion force.nnNow there's something I never expected to be a part ofan invasion force!

Ridiculous, that. The gathering, I mean. Do they not realize that we are endeavouring to satisfy them? Their conflicting demands and ridiculous expectations of time?nnTime marches only as it will. Such is its mandate.
We're to move on again. Of course. It is what our tribe does best.
Such bountiful waters  I'll miss fishing these shores.
Well, look who's here. It's nice to see a familiar face! Can you believe that the Mage Guild actually asked for our help? Expert consultants, they called us!
I remember you! I probably wouldn't be standing here today if it weren't for your help. Thanks!
Talk won't get us anywhere. Action! That's what will stop Molag Bal.
It's good to see you again, my friend!

The most painful thing about this scenario is the awareness they must lack of what we have already achieved for <<1>>.nnWe do not inform them because their lives are easier for not knowing. And this is the thanks we get.
Find out all you need to know?
Bah! I can't stand this glorified guard duty. Give me a skull to cleave!
You may have saved my life back in Stonefalls, but my master almost killed me for taking that tome!
After getting captured by those Goblins in Stonefalls, I've had my fill of them!
Bah. I don't trust your leader, and I don't trust you.
That's one ugly face you got there. Almost makes me look pretty. Ha ha!
If it isn't the hero of the alliance!
Your record with the Daggerfall Covenant has been exemplary. For that you have the High King's gratitude.

Are you off on a lovely little jaunt with that half-breed warrioress and her shrunken stooge of a lover? I hope you enjoy yourself in that decrepit pit. I'd love to join you, but The Prophet and I have other matters to attend to.
Shornhelm. It may be run-down, rainy, and ravaged by war, but  at least they've got ale!nnHow about you buy us another round?
The secret to curing the Baroness lies within this stone shard and the Ayleid relic it once belonged to.
Count Verandis. Hello. It's  um  good to see you. I hope you're well.nnWhat am I saying? Of course you're well! You're a vampire! Oh, sorry. Don't mind me. I must have had a little too much wine.
That's all there is to it! Welcome to the fold, scamp! You may one day have as many notches in your axe as I do. nnAw, who am I kidding? No you won't! Hah!
Riches and wealth pale in comparison to hard earned glory.nnI wouldn't sell my scars for anything in Tamriel.
I see they teach neither judgement, nor manners where you're from. This table is for the Undaunted.nnBegone!
I've got no more advice to give. Scurry off and see that you don't get yourself killed.
Thank you for your help with the carnival! The customers are starting to stream on through.
You interested in a drink? We have plenty to go around, considering the carnival is more or less shut down.
I don't even mind that we're not drawing in the crowds yet. I needed a break from that repetitive windbag, Noryon.
Some men call at the inn to meet and talk with strangers. I am not one of those men.
I don't trust those bugs. They haven't done much since I've been here, but I'm going to keep an eye on them all the same.
And that's our special Undaunted song. Did it hurt to hear as much as it did to sing it?
<<1>> is confused. She doesn't remember inviting you to keep her company, yet here you are. Curious.
The magic act is amazing! I can't wait for the Storyteller to get started. I love listening to old fairytales and legends.
This one hopes the Hollow City finds you well, Undaunted.nnMeridia's wayward township is many things, but it's never dull. Especially for an Undaunted.
To be honest, I don't mind the carnival not being full operational. I prefer shopping to spectacle.

Greetings, bold adventurer! I am <<1>>, servant of the Daggerfall Covenant and honorary member of the Undaunted. It's truly a pleasure to meet you.nnI'm told the newest members buy the drinks around here. What do you say, friend?
The Undaunted have no time for weaklings or beggers.
Quite the tail, eh? Get it? Tail?nnSeeks-Her-Glory  has a tail!
You don't look like an Undaunted to me.nnGet out of herewhile you still can.
Give me an excuse, and I'll eat your brains from your skull and drink your blood.nnThis table's for the Undaunted only.
What do you want, dungheap?
Hey, if it isn't my favorite fresh meat! Hope you've seen more combat than I have. Taverns only hold their charm for so long.
I don't know you. I don't want to know you. Go away.
<This Orc is either asleep, or ignoring you.>
This room's for the Undaunted, stranger. Undaunted only.
I have much better things to do than converse with you.
My wit's as quick as my blade.nnDon't believe me? Buy me another drink and I'll show you.
I'm reading and you're standing in my light. Be kind and stand somewhere else. Preferably outside so that I won't be forced to look at you.
My scales are dry, my tongue is drier. Though the blood of a miser could quench just as well as a cool drink.
This is a gathering for Undaunted.nnAnd you're no Undaunted.
This one doesn't have time for strangers. Sorry. This one has an entire loaf to finish.
If it isn't the new blood! Just in time, too. My mug is empty.
Don't talk to me. I might vomit on your shoes.
This grass itches. Please stop distracting me. I'm waiting for other Undaunted to come along. They're sure to need my advice or my wares.
I can't wait for another adventure to sweep me along.nnNothing out here but trees. You can't stab trees. Well, you can. But they don't stab back.
Open air is nicer than I thought it'd be. At first I was angry they threw me out of the tavern. But now pretty good.nnNow  pretty good.
I am not entirely sure what's going on outside.nnI doubt it really matters, in the grand scope of thingspeasants being peasants, I assume.
Dominion troops encroaching on our land? I wish they would all fall off a cliff!
The Dominion soldiers have no right to set up camp outside of town. This is our land, not theirs.
This grass itches and pricks. But it's much better than the cold.
I'm Earrona Kneecapper. If you want to know why they call me that, keep talking.
Unless you're secretly a magic being made of moon-sugar and ale, this one doesn't want to talk to you.nnThis one would also speak to Undaunted, but you look the opposite of that.
I think its best you step, away, friend or else I'll have to embarass you in front of these ladies.
I don't have time for the likes of you.
Do you always walk this close to people you don't know? Nevermind, I don't care. Just go away.
No, I don't need any more drinks, thank you.
The Empress of Bone is thirsty. Buy her a drink! Now!
I'll not forget your generosity, my friend.
Excuse me. You are in my light. We are establishing a scene here.nnYou are interfering in art. Please leave.

Whatever you intend to do while here, please refrain from interfering with my model.nnIt has taken me ages to coerce him into catching the light as he has. Any interruption and he might throw a tantrum and storm off.

I always admired Syrabane. Someday, I hope to be so well-known in Altmeri culture as that particular hero-sorceress.nnIt shall not, I expect, be through my diligent bookkeeping and efficient management skills that I become so well-known.
I've killed fools dumber than you before but I'm not sure I've killed anyone uglier. You don't want to be another notch on my axe. Beat it!
I'm in no mood. Leave before I finish my ale or you'll wish you had.nnMy drunk arm is a stiff arm, I assure you.
Ale in my belly and a story to pass around. That's all I need in life.
Let me know if you hear of any packing and unpacking jobs, would you?
My performers can best explain their setbacks. <<1>> is our bug trainer, <<2>> our storyteller, and <<3>> is  well, she's magnificent.nnI have to describe her that way. It's in her contract.
Dear me! Thrice the champion, is it? Bravo!
You are the one who cleared the Bjoulsae Boys out of Viridian Watch, yes? nnHmph. Quickpaw thought they were helping the poor all this time. What a fool I was.
<<1>> seems like a fancy device. I hope it works.nnAnd if it doesn't, I trust you'll keep the king safe? He's usually not so reckless.
Thank you again, my comrade-in-arms. It was a pleasure to fight at your side.

There won't be much to see, I'm sure. The Ayleids were notorious for their glowing crystals, so I suppose there will be more than a few bright lights.nnSounds quite dreary. I can't imagine it will be worth your time at all.
You've been stumbling all over Redfur like a mead-soaked goat. Is there a party somewhere I missed? There had better not be.nnI hate missing parties.

I, Boeuf Sterone, have noticed everyone has been acting oddly lately. Is there something happening?nnYou can tell your friend Boeuf Sterone if anything is. Trust in Boeuf Sterone, his word is as good as his food.
Hello! I have many fine pots and pitchers, and inside many of them, many fine things to drink.nnYou wish to trade for any of these things?
I don't trust this <<1>> one bit. He's an obsequious lickspittle, if you ask me.
Welcome to our humble guildhall, fellow Fighter. How are things out there?nnI'm itching to return to active combat.
I'm not doing anything until that coal fire is started. nnDon't worry, I'll be able to hear the blast from here.
Welcome, Mage. Feel free to make use of our humble facilities here as you will.nnThey are here for Mages Guild use, after all.
Have we met? You seem quite familiar.nnI'm demonstrably busy at the moment. It seems a colleague of mine couldn't avoid a simple spiritual posession on <<1>>. You understand, I'm sure.
It's good to see you. <<1>> has been assisting me with a  certain project. Before long, <<2>> will be free to leave <<3>>.nnSoon, I'm certain of it.

Ah, my friend from <<1>>. Rest assured, we're doing everything in our power to free my apprentice. <<2>> will not hold her for long.nnForgive me, I must return to my calculations. The magic is quite delicate.
I've been supplying the Briars for some time now. But I would be more than happy to take your coin as well.
<<1>> is my husband, and a master hunter. We met each other while stalking the same bear. It was love at first sight!
Good luck in your trials.
Don't ask what happened while you were drunk. It is better not to know.
The Dominion is in need of capable citizens. And by capable, I mean you.
Brendar returned safely thanks to you. I appreciate your kindness and bravery.nnHe's waiting at the Horker's Tusk. I believe he wanted to speak to you.
You made it out. That's good to see. What of the necromancer?
I can't believe that <<1>> is dead. She was a good soldier. And a good woman. She will be missed.
Bring this here, take it there. Half the time, it seems they're moving it just to have it moved!
This one brought his family all the way to <<1>>, expecting a place in our own embassy.nnInstead, we sit in leaky tents waiting for promises to be fulfilled!
They're going to have a feast for us? Is that what she said? I hope they don't serve any harpy meat. I never want to smell that again.
You're back. Need me again?nnI'd like to get out and about. There're too many memories that catch up when I'm not moving.
I have never idled well. I appreciate you bringing this old man along with you.nnIt feels good to put these hands to work.
I must confess. Before you returned, I felt somewhat lost, adrift. Traveling with you gives me purpose again.nnI don't do well while idle, it seems.
You should probably speak to Countess Tamrith. I'm not an official member of this triumvirate.
Every day is an adventure when you're part of the Ravenwatch, yes?
I can't believe this! I should cut my losses with these idiots. Work on my own!
What is going on? Why are the harpies attacking? You look like you can handle yourself, get out there and help.
You've ruined us. We'll have to find a new way to earn a living!
Poor Crestshade! What a disaster!nnI was about to head up to that House Ravenwatch stronghold to find help, but for some reason I can't seem to make my legs carry me up these stairs.
Sithis smiles upon <<1>>. Even so, it would appear he has business elsewhere.nnI overheard Dominion soldiers. They said they captured <<Ac:2>>. A dark day, indeed.
You sure you know where you're going? If you're looking for a shortcut to Shornhelm, I'd look elsewhere.nnI wouldn't walk into these ruins unless I knew what I was getting into.
I'm glad we've had someone like you on our side, from start to finish, if you catch my meaning.

You followed through? Excellent. I worried he'd convince you to set him free, then we'd have had to track down both of you. That would have been unpleasant.nnForget that, though. Can't tell you how glad I am to finally have this bastard in custody.
Go on, then. The bandits could be pulling up camp as we speak. If Gavendien gets away, I'll never forgive myself.
I thought that if we just cooperated with them, everything would work out and no one would be hurt.nnNow I know. I will never bargain with bandits again.
If I was a few years younger, I'd go after Gavendien myself. That rotten coward. Killing an innocent woman. He deserves to die!
It might be best for you to move on to another town. Hoarfrost Downs is nice this time of year, I understand.
No. I'm not coming. No, I'm not. Don't even ask. I'll come back, but only when Gaillard says it's safe. Yes, that's right. Only when Gaillard says.nnGaillard told me to stay right here until then.
I feel terrible. Poor Lauravieve. To die so young and so needlessly. It just isn't right.
Someone needs to find that Gavendien and make him pay!

My mother had a passion for jewels and jewelry, and she built this business from nothing.nnI never thought I'd wind up running it myself. Without her, I'm not sure I have what it takes. I'm going to try though.
Mark my words. No Orc gets by here as long as the King's Guard still stands.
I don't see anyone from the Ring of Daggers. Does that mean  you've chosen to let me go free?

It's hard for me to relate to someone like Julien. The young men in my home town never even noticed me. I tried to get their attention by challenging them to duels. But when I beat them, that just made it worse.nnSo I joined the Shornhelm Guard.
Do your worst, lackey to a foreign crown! I won't tell you anything!

At the moment, we're still trapped beneath Lleraya's veil. See if you can find another tear in the spell so that we can leave this place.nnI just hope the book is still with us when the illusion dissipates.

Remember, I'd like to save Northpoint while causing as little death and destruction as possibleexcept for the Montclairs. Kill as many of them as you like.nnJust remind Skordo that this is our city we'll be assailing, not some bandit stronghold.
I am praying for strength and courage. I should not be hiding from those foul creatures. But Arkay bless me, they make my skin crawl.
Good luck. Did I mention there's trolls around there? Frankly, they are worse than ghosts. Meaner and they small really bad.
Darien can't talk right now. I gave him something to relieve his pain. And to quiet him down for a little while.nnThe man does love the sound of his own voice.
I'll give the signal. It's time to liberate Northpoint from these monsters.nnMeanwhile, go to my manor and evict Montclair's daughter from the premiseswith extreme prejudice.
You may not believe this, but that wasn't how I wanted our reunion to play out. But laws were broken. People died. I can't ignore our laws.nnNot even to save my son.

Do you believe that man? And to think, I thought him to be dashing and heroic! But enough of such matters. You aren't here to discuss my personal life.nnTell me, what news from Count Ravenwatch? Are we ready to march against Montclair?
Rivenspire needs Tamrith and Dorell. They cannot be allowed to perish here.nnI need to help get them to safety before I join you up above.
And so everything returns to the way it should be, yes? Only I think the Baroness will be a little less quick to follow in her mother-in-law's footsteps, from now on.
Federic and <<1>> have both left. Perhaps I should leave, as well. Perhaps the Mages Guild has a place for me.
Thank you again, for convincing me to stay. With Federic leaving to join the Covenant, the Edralds will need me more than ever.nnAnd  it is good to see Arlie safe and sound.
Such an awful place. I could have lived my entire life without knowing of such things.
I am sorry to see <<1>> go, but it really is for the best. Soon my Arlie will be happily married, and we can all get on with our lives!
How vile! Is that a piece of Goveled's brain on your boot? What are you? Some kind of monster?nnOnly joking around, of course. You beat him, huh? I'm impressed.
There you are! I've been looking all over for you.nnVerandis requests your presence at the ruins in the Lorkrata Hills, if you aren't too terribly busy at the moment.
I don't know if I'll ever get used to traveling by portal. One moment you're there, the next moment you're here. It's positively disconcerting!
Doubt is insidious. It clouds the mind, makes it hard to think. And what I need, now, is to be thinking clearly!
It's an honor to see you again, my friend. May the gods bless you for all of your days!
Be at ease, friend. You may come anew to the race, just as the spring rains come anew after the winter's snow.nnI will review the rules with you again just to be sure that all is clear.
I don't think there's anything more for us to talk about.
Rohlbert is so brave, acting through hired assassins and spies. Let's see how brave he is when Adusa and Five-Claws come to call!
I hope my daughter finds a way to be happy. I know Federic cares for her, but I'm just not sure he'll satisfy her  more adventurous desires.
Don't worry. I'm keeping a tight watch on her. No more odd behavior. She promised! And I intend to hold her to that.
I will never be able to adequately apologize for everything that happened at the estate. But I am very appreciative that you supported our love.
Dulkhi and I will never forget what you did for us. We've never been more in love!
Verandis  why did it have to be you? Damn you, Verandis! Why didn't you tell me what you planned to do?
This must have been a room for prayer or peaceful contemplation when the Ayleids were alive.
The stars have accepted you. I just hope it is not too late.nnVolumes of prophecy have been written about the stars, but not even the oracles foresaw these events.
I'm just so happy   I can't stop crying.

Let me take a look at you. So you're the one who dispatched my father's pet Argonian? Well done, by the way. Well done.nnI'm so glad you're here. I was becoming dreadfully bored with Ellic and the rest of these silly nobles.
This chamber has a calming effect. I wonder if this was where the pilgrims rested on their way to visit the uppermost chamber?

I can't tell you how much I appreciate you convincing me to enlist. I've come to realize that this is what I was born to bea soldier.nnNot only have I been able to better support my family, but I like to think I've made them proud, too.
Well, we're here all right, but I'm not sure I'm going to be getting off the boat. In fact, I say we just put right back out to sea.

A finer group of soldiers never served in the Shornhelm Guard. Julien and Shuga have both turned out to be valiant warriors.nnAnd Martin's distinguished himself, too. I actually think he's got the makings of a strong leader.
Ah! You're one who killed that old skeever Dark Elf I was seeing! What was his name again ?nnNo matter. I owe you, though. This soldier business is a lot more fun than being a bandit!

If it isn't Mara's messenger in the flesh! You really saved my love-life. Looking back, I can't imagine what I ever saw in Guendeline. nnI finally met my true love during training. Shuga. She's sweet and strong and all the woman I'll ever need.
That old Khajiit lady in the wagon read my palm and told me that is where I needed to be for my luck to change.nnI'm staying right here until it does.

With all the trouble brewing outside these walls, I'm expecting a lot of orders for weapons soon. Unfortunately, I'm already overtaxed. We haven't had any steel shipments arrive in ages.nnI suppose we have to take the bad with the good.
There are things in these signs I don't understand. When you return, perhaps their meaning will become clearer to me.
I'm afraid the situation in Craglorn grows worse daily. We need every strong sword arm and spellcaster we can recruit.

I didn't put any stock in the words of those Star-Gazers until I saw my first sand giant. It cut a horse in half. I haven't run so fast since I was stealing meat on the streets of Riften.nnNow we're all listening a bit more closely.

Many Dwarven religious texts refer to a Dwemer site called Mtharnaz. A high priest named Arnming wrote that he wished to be buried there, "among the masters of the heavenly stone."nnHis burial site is our best chance of finding a Skystone amulet.

Be wary. This area is crawling with Worm Cultists. We learned that the hard way when they ambushed us down in the cavern.nnGods only know what they're doing down there, but we can't complete our mission.
We are near Fallowstone Hall, hallowed home of the Companions. I would show you around, but this is not your place.
I came up wth the name Outside Inn, because we're just outside of the Elden Root. Get it? Outside Inn?  I'm pretty clever that way!
Now that the city is safe and those Montclair miscreants have been banished, I think I'll just sit here for awhile and soak up the ambiance.

Well, at least Shornhelm is safe. For now. But I can't stand the way Baron Dorell and Countess Tamrith bicker. And in public, even!nnI wonder when the two of them will decide to settle their differences by the sword?
The High King gave the crown of Shornhelm to Baron Dorell. I mean, King Alard. That's what we call him now. And he looks so handsome in his regal garb!
The High King crowned the Countess! Excuse me, Queen Eselde. That's what we call her now. And she looks beautiful in her regal garb!
I heard we have a queen now. I wonder if things will really get any better.
So the High King gave the crown to Countess Tamrith. Well, that figures! He always had a soft spot for beautiful Eselde.
Welcome to the Shornhelm Mages Guild Hall. Do I detect a budding acolyte in our midst?
Thank the Lord, Mother, and Wizard. You're back! nnPlease tell me you've got good news.
Ahh, you're back. Sorry about earlier. I'm feeling better already.nnWhat news from the spider hole?
Ah, you're back. Do you have my goods?
Greetings, traveler. You'll go no further up the river here, I'm afraid. A mystical ward bars the path up to Tormented Spire. An unstable ward, at that.
Good luck. Kyne speed you on your way.

Pardon me; I'm seeking a group that will offer me protection on my trip.nnI'm a researcher of sorts, seeking out the secrets of Craglorn! But I can't do it all by myself. If you haven't noticed, things haven't been friendly as of late.
We can handle ourselves for now, but I don't know how long we can keep this up.nnSee what they need at Vivec's Antlers first. That's the higher priority right now.
Covenant soldiers everywhere. Like an infestation of nasty, stinging mudcrabs. Bah.
Hello, friend.
Report in, soldier. What brings you to Vivec's Antlers?
You arrive alone. Either you didn't find him, or I need a new hunting partner.
My friend! How good to see you again! Did you give the Hagraven a proper thrashing? And did you happen to find my wife's mace?nnTell me all is well and we'll drink to our good fortune!

Thank you for returning my mace. My husband always loses things, and he refuses to put on a decent pair of shoes, but I do love him so.nnAs soon as he's sober, though, we're going to have a talk about why I remind him of a Hagraven.
You found my cat!
Let's look around the perimeter of the camp. The remains of the last soldier must be around there somewhere.
You should be able to find <<1>> toward the front of the camp. That's where I saw him last.

We've been in Stormhaven fighting the Ironhand Ogres for too long. We've got soldiers stationed here, Wayrest  all across eastern Stormhaven, really.nnWe need to do our duty for the Covenant, but at some point, we need to go home to Wrothgar.

You don't look like someone who's just wandering by. Please tell me you have word from General Godrun or someone over at Shinji's Scarp.nnPlease tell me they're finally sending orders for us to rejoin the main army.
I know that look, friend. Is the task complete? Are Lleraya's remaining vampires destroyed?
I feel better already. Just knowing that I reached out to Azura. I know my father would be pleased as well.
These are dark times, my friend. I only pray that Azura can speed the dawn of brighter days to come.
Remember to bring any messages you find to Captain Gilame up near the tower.
This is a bad time for Kragenmoor, traveler. Are you here on business? If not, you'd best be moving along.
You saved me, and helped free my father's city. I have no doubt you'll put a stop to this madness.
Thrice-blasted nobles! Their coffers keep the kingdom running, but at the first sign of trouble .
Welcome to Hoarfrost Downs, perhaps the dreariest hamlet in all of Rivenspire. Actually, the entire kingdom is rather dreary, isn't it? nnWhat can I do for you? Have you come to join the Mages Guild?
Hail, comrade. You'll have to pardon my appearance. Tangled with a Clannfear recently and this Coldharbour muck stains worse than the snowberry wine.
Baron Dorell sends us out here to get the drop on Montclair, and what happens? The fiend turns half of Northpoint into gibbering monsters and we're stuck waiting for orders!

Fenila's words are incorrect, Lord Vivec, though she clearly believes them. I haven't contacted Belronen for months, and would never have done so without your direction.nnWealth has no meaning next to serving you, my lord. This you know to be true.

Lord Vivec, Vamen should be dead on the floor. Belronen wouldn't share the note that temple netch sent his way, but assured me its contents were vile.nnOne sworn to the temple, quibbling over coin? You should kill him yourself. My lord.

A tragedy, Lord Vivec. Belronen's death in the temple brings great shame to his house. I had thought reasoned words could dissuade him from the duel.nnSuch temper is common to House Telvanni. But it's not my place to question their reliability.

The Wilderking's reign draws to an end. The forest spirits have gone mad, even my own brethren  and he is powerless to stop them. nnIntruders enter Greenheartdark and conflicted soulsthey are the harbingers of the Wilderking's death.
Don't tell the Commander who sent you to him. His mood's been an icy squall since Thod failed to report in this morning. The last thing I need is him taking it out on me.
Don't you worry. We'll see those reserves are sent. In the meantime, I have a favor to ask. I have a missive that must reach Vulkhel Guard.
Enjoy the pomp and circumstance, friend. I'll keep the mugs warm for the royals. Heh.
Is my brother ready? I need to get him out of here.
You've made me a happy man. Thank you!
The Maulborn tricked us? Those fetchers!nnAnd to think I drank three of their curatives.
I see Aerona has conscripted a new soldier into her private army.
You're not going to find my siblings here. I can tell you that for sure.

It is good to see you again, my friend! Greenshade is a far more exciting place than Raz expected.nnHe hears now that the Staff of Magnus has been stolen? As if these rebellious Bosmer weren't trouble enough!
We will always be grateful to you.
We're a family again thanks to you!
You have to help them!
Have you brought me a sweet? I love sweets.
I'm afflicted. I just know it.
So cold  I'm so very cold .
Who knew that loam and animal skins could make such delightful flooring? I tell you, the stone in most guild halls are murder on my feet. But I do ramble.
You'll find the portals further into the sewers.

You need to convince my sister to leave this place. Then you can deal with the Maulborn.nnDestroy their ability to make more of this damn plague. Just be careful. The chamber ahead is crawling with plague husks.
You provide a welcome distraction, friend. The thought of those Jackdaw brutes muddying my floors and soiling my instruments is too much to bear.
You look lost. Can't say I blame youElden Root can be quite a labyrinth, but you've found the most important branch! The hall is at your disposal.
It's always nice to meet a fellow pilgrim on the path to enlightenment. There are all manner of secrets tucked away in this forest. Just have a care around the plant-life. It can be  temperamental.
I wish I'd studied my cleansing spells more diligently. It'll take days to wash the dog-stink out of this room. nnBut please forgive my grumbling. You're most welcome in our hall.
You have to help them!
What a relief to see a fellow arcanist. I trust that the barbarians across the hall didn't give you too much trouble? Their grunting and laughing and howling is just  incessant.
What a mess. You don't need a tour of the facilities, do you? Judging by the Orc blood on the carpet, I'd wager this isn't your first visit.
It's good to see another mage who's not afraid of the outdoors. While other mages dodder around their guild halls, we sleep under the stars and make new discoveries daily. What an adventure!
Patience. Yes. Painful as it may be to practice, it can be a formidable weapon when mastered.nnI just have to keep reminding myself of that.
Yes? It's nice to see you again, of course, but I am kind of in the middle of something here.
If anyone knows how to stop this, the Aldarch will. Go, you have to help her!

The loss of life is always tragic, but death is a critical part of nature's cycles. Some things must perish, so that others may thrive.nnSuch is the case here. Though you may mourn for these Bosmer, know that you protected the Valenwood.
If anyone knows how to stop this, the Aldarch will. Go, and may the blessings of the Eight be upon you.
Bah! These classifications are all wrong. We will never unravel the secrets of this place if we can't even label our discoveries properly. Perhaps a new indexing system would help .
I'm happy that the mine is back under our control, but I can't shake this bad feeling I have.
Another associate climbs aboard our rickety "guild hall." And hey, since you're already a member I don't have to give you my guild recruiting pitch.nnPraise Vivec.
Have I convinced you, then? Are you ready to join up?
I knew you figure it out! Please hand the potion to Nilyne so she can inspect your results.
Please, let me teach what I can to Erunor while there's still time. See if you can do something for what's left of our poor village.
Move along, citizen. By order of <<1>>, these godless fanatics and their sorry excuse for a shrine are off-limits until the talks in <<2>> have concluded.
Didn't you hear what I said? Out! The patient needs time to let the potion work its magic.
You did it! Good job! Now give the potion to Nilyne and see what she thinks of your technique.
It's times like these when I wish I had more help around here.nnIs there something I can get you?
Glad you aren't scared off like some other folks. You'd think they'd never seen another Bosmer before.
You know, I used to have dreams of becoming an adventurer like you and journeying all over Tamriel  and then I realized, it's so much easier to just stay at home.
Hello there. Welcome to Bramblebreach. If you came to see a festival, I'm sorry. It's the off-season right now.nnOf course, you're always welcome to stay and join us for music and dance!
Remember what we talked about and this will all turn out very profitable for everyone involved.
What do you say? Do you have what it takes? Are you ready to join the fight?
I heard something happened to Hara. I'm really scared. I'm thinking about returning to Mournhold.
The Maulborn curative was a lie? Then that means there's no hope for my wife. No hope at all.
Hello again, my slick-scaled friend. Have you been to Emberflint yet? And did I ever tell you about the Armature?
The Maulborn stink of deceit and treachery. I spit venom in their general direction!
I guess I should be thankful the Maulborn ignored us. Still rude of them, though.
As soon as the plague husks are gone, we're going to go into the catacombs and see what valuables the Maulborn left behind.
Is it hot in here?
Twelve scaly Argonians, all baked in a pie .

I'm feeling so much better. But Nilyne says her potion has only suppressed the plague, not cured it.nnIf you find a way to beat this plague, make sure you send word to us. And thanks for helping our town.
You keep coming back to talk to me. If you're trying to get my attention, you're going to have to do better than that.
Traveler. How goes your survey of Zabamat? Have you found Mephala's Nest, yet?
Helgana will soon be with her ancestors in Sovngarde. The vile Covenant soldiers of Softloam Cavern have seen to that.nnMay the Lord, Mother, and Wizard watch her on her journey.
<Pain has overwhelemed Helgana. She stares without seeing.>
So the Maulborn lied to us? That is what I said the moment they first came to the Serk.nnDark Elves never listens to Argonians. They yell at us, but they never listen.
You mean there isn't any cure? I guess this is what true disappointment feels like.
What's going on around here? We heard that there is no curative. That it was all a lie.nnWhat are my brothers going to do now?
I'll be in to help as soon as I can. Just catching my breath, that's all.
My sweet Mirilir. I would say that I miss him, but I know that I will follow him soon enough. I am ready now.nnBut you, you're so kind. Did you find the Nereid's Smile?
I recognize you. You were talking with Urcelmo in the courtyard earlier. I heard about what happened with Astanya  most of us aren't like that. Will you spare a moment for the true Vulkhel Watch?
Thank the Stars. This mudcrab won't stop pinching me. nnListen, you have to get to Silsailen! Help them before it's too late.
They've burned the town! Please, please help us!
I knew the curative was too good to be true. Now I suppose the plague is going to kill us all.

Big hullabaloo about this girl, that boy. Pfft! Let them do what they will, I say.nn"Hullabaloo"? Where did I pick up such a vulgar word? Must be Bosmer. I'll need to stay out of Elden Root for a while.
I just arrived from Deshaan. Dethisam sent me. Perhaps you've heard of him? He's the consul for the town of Serkamorathe Serk.nnI'm here to spread the word and warn people about the Llodos plague.
Talk to Sali'ma. Half of our research team drank the water before we realized what was happening.nnEnding whatever curse is on the water might be our only chance to save them.
I was so relieved to get that letter from my cousin. Between knowing that he's all right and hearing that the Maulborn have a cure for this plague, I'm feeling so much better.
We've done nothing to them! Why do they attack us?

Light the four keyflames to unseal the pathway into the underground. Once there, deal with as many of the escaping monsters as you can. There's no telling what could be down there, but I think it's safe to say it's a threat to us all if set loose.
Thank you for talking to me. Auri-El only knows what I've had to put up with out here. That old goat won't listen to a word I say!
You can find Erold in our observatory, up on the top of the hill.
<<1>> thought Marbruk was a brand new city, but it is very popular already! Even the royalty visit.

I'd only finished the first trial when the betrayer struck, but it stands to reason that he's in the most secure part of the schoolthe cavern at the end of the final trial.nnYou'll need to complete the trials in order to avenge us.
Hara seems to have a great amount of faith in you, my friend. I'll make sure your name is never forgotten by history.
You approach, knowing what you want! I was once like that, not that long ago. Please, share some gold with poor Kuralit?
You enter my temple once more, Seeker. What knowledge have you brought me?
My word, Queen Ayrenn, visiting Marbruk! A pity the streets hadn't been cleaned up before her arrival.nnThat said, what business do you have with us today?
It didn't work. I wasn't able to shield myself from the nightmares.nnShe is  she is gone. I couldn't save her.
Ah, you're back! Don't look so gloomy. At least you made it back to fight another day.nnMy allies weren't so lucky. Well? You're breathing, aren't you? Get back out there!

Who are you? How have you come to avenge us? You will find few allies here.nnAbelazar the betrayer has turned all of the Sword-Disciples into thralls. He would have turned me as well, if I had been less of a coward.

So it is true then? Prince Naemon has been raised from the dead and now seeks vengeance by corrupting Valenwood?nnGods help us! That makes this even more difficult. And with the undead already outside the city gates, we must act now.
The captain. They  they came at night. We couldn't .
Hermaeus Mora is waiting to speak to you. Just approach his shrine and listen to what he has to say.
Forgive me. I did not know any other way to contact you without revealing myself. Even now, the Serpent's followers, the Scaled Court, are searching for me.
It's true, no rest for the weary.
target: vero, non c' nessun riposo per gli stanchi.

source: You're still alive! I mean, of course you are. It's just like the goblets said.nnLooks like the water barrier is down as well. We must be close to the Water of Life now.
Thank you kindly. You'll find <<1>> on the west path into town. Hurry back now.
Good luck, my friend. Wherever your travels take you next, know that you have all of the Guild at your back.
Tu'whacca speed you on your travels, and may the sand not slip beneath your sandals.

Ah. Just the one Raz was waiting for. The queen needs someone who can be entrusted with a  dignified task, and this one cannot currently oblige.nnYou would be acting as Ayrenn's personal envoy, but you can be respectable, yes?
Divines bless you, friend! World's a hard place, these days. My eleven children will surely starve today without a morsel to eat.nnWon't you spare some gold for an honest man and his poor children?
Five  no, ten! Ten bandits beat me and made off with my belongings! All they left were these rags you see before you. The pain! It is without ending!
By the Egg, I've never felt such hunger. But with no gold to buy it .
Hey burr-sap! Spare a glint? A peck of shiny gems?
Always good to see a fellow member.
We need to double our membership. This is the third Guild Hall this month to be overrun!
How is the arena here? You think the lizards will let me fight without taking their stupid trial? Looks like a good time. I should ask.
None of these pirates want to join the Fighters Guild. I tried telling them Daedra could be found on the seas, but that just made them nervous.
Did my brother send you? I've been expecting a shipment for more than a week now.
Be careful in there. Those Red Rook bastards are as deadly as they are ugly.
You probably want to talk to one of the crafters.nnUnless, of course, you're looking for some hot coals.
I hope you'll forgive me for just accosting you out there like this, but my master sent me to find you. nnSomething  terrible has happened and she says we need your help.

Ah! So he did find you? That's good. The Ebonheart Pact needs a hero here. King Jorunn needs a hero here.nnThe Worm Cult's leaderThallik Wormfatherhe's a sneaky one, and very dangerous. Whatever he's planning, he must be stopped.

At this point, I'm not looking for a cure. These waters make you insane. Muttering this "Shada this" and "Shada that" nonsense. Not to mention trying to rip out your throat.nnDo what you have to do and just get any survivors out of there.
I don't know how you did it, but this water's as clear as the desert sky.nnI'm not going to drink any of it, mind you. But it seems safe to touch.

So many people from all over Tamriel called Elinhir home. nnEvery morning, the magic students gathered in the city center to practice their spells. I'd open my butcher's stall while dazzling beams of light and color cut through the morning air.
I  need to catch my breath. Good luck against Yamanu-ko .
Good job! Now you've got to kill the other beast!
That core is looking less stable by the second. We must hurry!

The journal mentioned rain. Nerien'eth must have cast the ritual in an outdoor space. It shouldn't be far.nnBe on your guard. He'll show no mercy if we meet, and that Daedric artifact he wields casts an ill aura.
Find Zal'ik and release me from my imprisonment in this place. Then I will share with you what I know about cleansing the water of Shada's curse.
I don't understand. What's happening? Why Hara? Why now?
It wasn't so long ago that I had not even heard of this Worm Cult. Now these Worms are everywhere, killing people, destroying villages .nnThis has to stop.
Who are you? Are you in league with this Thief? I demand that you free me immediately!

With the Treeminder dead, we could kill this Hist, end its story here and now. Or simply leave it alone. Without the Treeminder, it cannot see, cannot feel. I would inflict both, if I could.nnMy sisters were granted no mercy. I will grant none.
You have done what the Yokudans could not. You have slain Zal'ik. You have given me my freedom.nnAnd yet, forgive me if I feel no joy. Zal'ik was a brave man. He only wanted to save his people.
This book could hold a cure and even more that we do not yet know.nnIt will be invaluable to us.
You didn't die! I mean, of course you didn't die. I had absolute faith in you.
If we're going to learn what happened to the atronachs, you must rescue Kelmen Locke from the Greycloak mercenaries.
You must find and defeat the air monarch. An atronach with the power of three monarch atronachs is just too dangerous.
You have my thanks friend.
You turned the tide for us, my friend. I was sure we were done for at least a dozen times today.
Hail, comrade! Quite a hike to get up here, eh? Good! Helps build endurance. You'll need it out theretrust me.

Strange. I've seen these ruins jutting from the waters before. They always seemed so  ordinary. nnBut now they're practically humming with energy. And I sense  what is that  my gods, yes! It's some kind of entrance.
It looks a hopeless task to me, but something makes me want to believe Hara would not have sent us here if she wasn't sure we could find whatever it is she needs us to see.
Keep back from the platform.
Look what the cat dragged in!

Use this time to gather your allies, sharpen your skills and hone your reflexes. nnWe've won a great victory, but the war has only just begun. When the time is right to go on the offensive against the Serpent, I will call for you to lead us.
The Apex Stone rests below, in the sewers of Elinhir.nnThe Seeker's Sight will aid you once you get inside and help you find your way.
Do not fear for us. We will not let the Serpent devour us.nnWe will be the crack in the armor. You will be the blade that liberates us.
Meet me in the house.
I didn't expect to see your lovely face so soon, my friend. How was your little adventure?
I don't think it's a good idea to be looking through Danni's things.
I guess we're going to a party. I hope the drinks are at least passable.
Fast ship, yes?

Would you just look at these small alcoves. How marvelous! Hewn after the fall of the city, no doubt. Late Merethic Era, I should think. No, no. Earlier than that. I just . nnYou're not following any of this, are you? Typical.
Please, wayfarer, take a moment to replenish your supplies. You'll need them in there, of that I have no doubt.
I don't like this. I don't like being out here. We're too exposed! We should head back.
This one does not like us abandoning the camp. Not safe leaving our valuables behind. Malihaz needs more eyes  or a twin brother. Something.
Glad you're coming with us.

My brother drank some of that water. There was so much shouting! And he put his hands around my throat! If not for Malihaz, Ruptga knows what would have happened.nnStill, I love my brother. If you see him, please  be kind.
Welcome to the Lass! I am most pleased to see you. Can I get you something? A drink, perhaps?
I trust that you've come to harrass us like the others. Let me save you the effort. Until such time as we're physically removed, we will remain here to conduct our research. Now begone.
Let's get going, if you're ready. Jump in the boat and I'll untie us.
We must find the Mage's other aspects before the Serpent does.
Spare anything?
Hope you find what you're looking for.
Luck be with you.
The Lost One carries our thoughts, as we carry hers. But her mind is corrupted, and she reserves no place of affection for you in her darkened heart.nnShe will not hold back. Neither should you.
When we are whole, it will take all of our concentration to resist the Serpent's will.nnShould we fail to overcome his grip, you must strike us down. We will do our best to weaken our darker self.
We've got to reach the helmet first!
The Warden is dead. His prisoners freed. What fun this has been!nnYou've done well, for such a fleeting creature. I have found a new, and very slight, respect for mortal-kind.
No pressure, but I can't collect any used merchandise until you've dealt with it's previous owners.
Ah, very nice! Truth to be told, I'd have no way of knowing if you mined these yourself or got them from someone else but it's a fairly moot point.

You look like danger interests you.nnWhat would you say if I knew of a tower of mages that until recently was sealed for centuries, and that was so dangerous that no one has entered the upper halls and lived?
That doesn't surprise me at all. I have a feeling I know where she's going. As your first official duty with the guild, I'd like for you to accompany her.

"Step 1: Get Some Iron Orenn"Iron ore is the simplest to work. It's also cheap to replace if you make a mistake. The first thing you need is enough to work. When you have ten solid chunks of iron ore, you're ready for the next step."
Welcome to the crew, fish. You make an excellent dagger.
Stay away from <<1>>. He's a trained dog, that one. The magistrate tells him how and where to do his business.nnToday, it was all over <<2>>.
Hold it! This is Covenant territory, stranger. We'll take your coin, but if you make any sudden moves we're going to have a problemclear?
We have a ship, the guiding stone, and our initiate. I can't believe I'm saying this, but, I think we're ready.
Speak to my assistant. I'm busy.
I don't know how Vexa ever got anything done without me.
Are you really thinking of helping those crazy High Elves? Well, I guess it's your time to waste.

I don't know what you're up to, and I don't really care. Just stay out of our way. We've got work to do.nnYou might want to avoid the upper floors, while you're at it. There's no telling what the Learned One might do.
That mere mortals could best the Warrior so easily gives me pauseI question whether that kind of power belongs in mortal hands. But I thank you for your help.
I'll be returning to Belkarth soon. I just need to finish a few things here first.nnI might even bring some of this wine back with me. Stars know we could always use more wine at the observatory.
<An old Dwarven orrery. It contains nothing of interest.>

Another interruption? The Learned One has taught us much since her arrival, but undoing the Archive seal has had a  trying effect on our work.nnIf you insist on trampling through our facilities, stay away from the upper floor. For your own good.
All right. Boat's ready. I'm ready. Are you ready, rook?
You you made it back! Oh, I'm so relieved. Thank you for checking in. Danni will want to talk with you, but I'm glad to see you're okay.

We've not had visitors to the Aetherian Archive in a long time. You should know that you pose a risk to yourself by stepping outside this chamber.nnThe Learned One does not want outsiders on the upper floors. I would not test her.
Thanks for talking me out anything stupid, rook. I needed to vent my frustrations. Now, let's go steal a ship.
Without Hara, I fear we will all be swallowed by the darkness. Please help her.
I just heard what happened to Hara. What could this mean? Could it be that the Scaled Court has agents even among the Star-Gazers?
This one would not go near the Citadel again for all the Moon Sugar in Tamriel.nnActually, that's not true.

So you plan on approaching that Citadel, eh? You look like you can take care of yourself, but I'm telling youno one who's stepped out there has returned, be they scholar, merchant, or warrior.nnIt's your life.
You  you plan to venture within?nnI do not possess your bravery, but pleasemany of my friends, scholars, drivers of the caravans, have gone inside and not returned. Help them if you still can.
Glad you could meet me. The boat's all ready. I' just need to hear the word.
You're here. Good. Are you ready to go?
Hello there.
My friend, you're victorious!nnI hope Hel Ra Citadel was fierce enough for you!
Move along, please.
Grab that Eyes of the Queen disguise. It's our best protection while we infiltrate this place. I shall play the part of the gruff and lowly prisoner.
Make sure you take that Eyes of the Queen disguise. We'll need it for getting inside. Let's just hope we can fool the guards long enough to get Gwenneth.
Grab that disguise before we go in. We need it to get past the guards here. I don't know if it'll fool them for very long, but it's the best chance we've got.
HelloEnjoy your stay at Xarxes' Rebuke.
Kidnap me, will they? Ugh. This is such a waste.
Don't kill me! Please! I didn't kill the master!
The ship's new crew will work out. And if they don't, the captain will send them off to the old mutineers.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
It is good to see you up and about. I credit <<1>>'s sweet sea breezes with your recovery!
You are a good rider. This one will have to work harder to bring you a real challenge.
I had a horse. It threw me near Westry. I have not seen it since. But I will get another one, and it will not throw me, and I will prove myself.
Leave an old man be!
Rana's waiting for you in the village. Go on. She doesn't bite, though she looks like she might.
Stay back! If the guards see us speak, they'll beat us both!
Do not worry, my friend. The poison will do no lasting harm.nnTo her, I mean. She will need to burn her bedsheets.
Welcome to my humble home. What can Magistrate Banu do for you today?
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
This is Ahmat's childhood home, he says. If this one was a child here, this one would have run away from home.
When my horse is watered, I will try the race again. My dear mother did not raise me to give up at the first sign of trouble.
Good! What are you waiting for? Get going! Follow the markers until you reach the end.
If you see the queen, tell her where to find us. Tell her that Talaya has designed a challenge just for her, yes?nnThis one would be deeply honored to have her run the course.

These milk-drinkers and their skinny little steeds  I will show them how to ride a horse! As soon as I get a new mount, that is. nnMy mare was eating the colorful leaves, but they were apparently poisonous. No matter, I will find another!
It is dark place in which we meet today, my friend. I am sorry that you are here. I am sorry that I am here.nnBut if we are going to be stuck here, then we shall at least have a riding course!
Talaya needs to find that Cadwell. That old bastard better have some ideas for how to make the course more difficult.

If I am truly going to be stuck here for all eternity, maybe it's time I find something better to do. nnTo be honest, I never really liked Ahmat. At least once, you would think that stupid milk-drinker would have let me borrow his horse!
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Talaya hopes to see you again. Next time, perhaps she can build a course that you will not complete so easily!

Riding horses is in my nature. You can ask anyone in these parts. nnI was born on horseback. Literally. My mother was fleeing the Reachmen, and I just popped outright there on the rump of my father's prize-stallion. It's a shame that horse died.

It's not fair! I finally saved up enough gold to buy a new horse and then, before I even get to ride it, some skinny little Bosmer sneaks up and steals it!nnI'll find him somehow, even if I have to tear this forest apart!
This is fine. Talaya will simply have to redouble her efforts. She will make the course harder, yes?nnPerhaps  more roots? And maybe some hoarvoars .
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
As much as I love to ride horses, I would not do it here. nnMy legs are so sweaty from this heat and humidity, I fear I would just slide right out of the saddle!
Go on now. You must find another of our courses. Surely, there will be one you cannot complete so easily.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
You just wait. Talaya is no mewling, dull-clawed kitten. You want a hard course, this one will give it to you!
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Go on now. Talaya needs to retrace the course. She will figure out your trick, and she will amend the course so that others cannot complete it so easily.
Where is that Baandari? She promised me the fastest horse this side of Cyrodiil. I gave her the gold, now she had better deliver!
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Be on your way now. Talaya has already acknowledged your success. You do not need to remain here and tickle this one's whiskers.

This isn't fair! I paid a traveling a merchant a king's ransom to bring me a stallion from the Alik'r desert, and do you know what happened? Do you know?nnThe horse froze to death the night he arrived! I tell you, I am beginning to think I am cursed.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Every time you beat one of Talaya's courses, you challenge her to do better.nnIt is good to have a nemesis!
I was knocked off my horse and when I came to, it was gone.
This one wonders if she could make a course that runs through Oblivion .
Another course, another lost horse. It seems my luck has not changed.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
This one will be glad to be out of Rivenspire. Bloodfiends bite more than Talaya's little cousins.
Yes, I think I'm just about ready. Just give me a few more minutes here. I'm confident I will succeed.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
This one does not mean to complain. Talaya loves her work, she really does. But she prefers dry ground.
I'm thinking of hiring an Argonian guide to ride along with me. Maybe then things will go my way. nnOr not. Probably, he'll just rob me and leave for dead in the murk.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
You are a skilled rider. Talaya will have to be craftier to trick you.
I have wanted to be a Black Horse Courier since I was a young boy. It was a courier who brought news of the invaders who sacked my home. That man saved our lives.
I don't care to sail through corpses. But if I dock at Mistral, they'll inspect my cargo!nnWhich is all legitimate, I assure you.
