Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
Oh the pockets this one picked with her father showing her the way. Such fine memories!
I was the fastest rider in my village. As long as the finish line was less than a league away. The truth is, I'm more of a sprinter.
This is too convenient. A token, so you can be brought in? How did she know this would happen?nnSomething's awry. Danni knows more than I think she should.
Welcome! I take it you were brought here by one of our Guides.nnAre you to be our new initiate?
Please tell me we're ready to go, or that I can stop holding back on this delicious ale.
You missed my big performance! I was hoping you'd be here in time to watch. It was a great time.nnGot to peek in lots of windows.
Glad you could make it. I've been listening in to some conversations, and having a few of my own.
Thanks to you, the Thieves Guild is a success.
Hope to see you for the next big heist.
Now I wonder what will be next on the list.
I hope Danni has something amazing up her sleeve still left.
After you.
You're mising out on the instructions! Don't blame me should something go wrong.
Satakal's vengeance must be quick as a serpent's strike. You'll find my traitorous acolytes at Scaled Court enclaves throughout the region.
The Moons are pleased, walker. Very pleased.
Heading to Abah's Landing? I'm the captain you want to talk to.
Heading to Abah's Landing? I sail there quite regularly if you need a lift.
Abah's Landing by starlight. Have you ever seen such a gem of a city? I can take you there, if you wish it.
Any news about our missing guards? We're counting on you to see this through for us.
That look on your face. You look like you've been beaten. They beat me, tooI didn't let it bother me  by the Moons this hurts.nnYou're alive, aren't you? Get back in there!
Listen to me, my friend. We have a problem.
What're you doing down here? Flee, you fool! The Serpent is here, and his Scaled Court runs rampant through these caverns!

You'd best turn around, stranger. The Star-Gazers had reason to suspect Scaled Court activity in these caves, but it's not just the Courtthe Celestial Serpent is here! nnHe has plans for Craglorn. For all of Tamriel.

What do you want? Have you fools come to your senses? Ready to set me free?nnThe master will do it himself after he peels the skin off you! He will not suffer a member of his Court humiliated like this! I will not suffer it!
Little goat is still here? Why? Little goat has work to do! Don't come back until the task is done!
Don't worry. You have the Listener's favor at least.
I knew there was wisdom in you. You'll still need to report to the Listener, but I'm sure the Keeper will wish to speak to you about your actions here today.
I see you've returned from the mission I assigned you.
Make her pay.
I barely know her, yet she claims I ruined her life. And now my life lies in your hands. I'm begging you to reconsider. Take my offer and the Dark Brotherhood will have me as a loyal client.
Travys is a good  man. Been looking our for Lady Margrette and her family since she was a little girl.
Now let's see. Maybe if I get him something he doesn't like, he'll be more likely to  make a decision next time.
I'm serious about that offer. Can't say we get many that look quite as  capable as yourself.
I can't wait for tonight. It's going to be lovely.
I wouldn't go tellin' people that we spoke here.
Remember to let me know if you see her!
I'm telling you, her safety is all a facade. Travys knows. He just can't get the people good enough to hire for these posts.
'Bout time to call it quits, I think.
If anyone asks, we never spoke.
It looks like things went well. Where to now?
Hi! Lovely day to be in prison, isn't it? Can you be a dear and undo those locks for me, please? That would be very lovely of you.
You've been gone for some time. How'd it go?
Is the Covenant on our side or the Daedras'? Kill me or free me, but decide quickly.
Oh please, please don't kill me!
Welcome to the fortress of the so-called Free Legion. Per the Keeper's instructions, everyone here dies.nnAre you ready? You've got the first task.
Head inside, find Marganus. Let's see what you can do.

Did you come looking for the Scaled Court, too? Looks like the bastards have no shortage of enemies.nnYou have that look in your eye. If you're planning on going into these caves, you'll need equipment. Just so happens I have some I could sell you.
This place is fascinating, isn't it? As naturally beautiful as the cultists inside are deranged.nnSaywhile I have you here, how about you take a look at my wares?
Talk to Bronric. He'll take you to the Free Legion's Redoubt.
Now that it's been announced, We need to act fast. No one here is going to make any changes until they see the Wrath of Sithis is real. I'm sending you after the biggest violators we have.
Looking for the Listener?
Wonder where you've been all this time.
The Wrath of Sithis. That sounds  amazing.
Hurry! Up the hill! He's feeding my companions to the trolls!
I've heard of this "Captain Ann." Bah!
Ann's a jerk!
Considering I've lost two of my best, I'm turning to you for this latest contract. It's somewhat sensative, but I trust you'll handle it like the professional you are.
I'm going to keep working here. If Adreso is your target, you'll find him in the manor house.

Thanks to the bravery of people such as you, we scholars can do our own part to make the world a better place.nnI need to return to Dragonstar. My companions need to know what's happening here. When you find the Scaled Court, show them no mercy.
Do you approach us with darkest joy in your heart? Is the deed done?
Did it succeed? Do not lie to me. I do not respond well to deceit.
This is a very high level contract. I'm trusting you to see it through. Are you ready?
You're going into the Valley of Scars? You're certainly braver than I am.
What's the contract today?
Good luck, and may Tall Papa bring you and our friends back safely.
I wish I was healthy enough to go with you. Just promise you'll bring my Camaarie back to me in one piece.
Hope the Jarl gave you a good warm up. You're going to need it for this run.
Remember. Don't stop for anything. Run straight to the shoreline where Bronric dropped you off.
If you get a chance, make those Iron Orcs pay for what they did to us. A little blood for blood, know what I mean? It's only fair.
Heed me, Wrath of Sithis.
I thought I saw Veesk's techniques in all this. She does exceptional work!nnJust be careful. The mantikoras I've encountered are deadly enough. I can't imagine what this progenitor can do.
You've got quite a bundle there. Did you find our caches?
Thank you for untying me. I'll get out of here as quickly as I can!
You're one of those who fought the Scaled Court? Beat back the Iron Orcs? Thanks for that, I guess.nnNow if you only could do something about those Dragonstar Caravan Company criminals .
We were fortunate you arrived when you did. Nerien'eth single-handedly trounced the lot of us, even as we were fully prepared to face him.nnYou must be formidable indeed.
The Listener has been blessed with the silence of the Void.nnYou will enjoy a different form of silence, soon. I have a final task for you.
Varn seems to have come into her own. She's asked me to be her Keeper, which I can do.nnThis all seems fitting, like it was meant to be. We have a lot to do, but I feel more grounded, now.
It wants to know of Oosh? She is colder, sharper, like a well-honed blade.nnThe scales suit her well. I approve.
We're getting sicker by the minute. Please, hurry!
This is a private matter, and your presence draws attention. I do not require the Wrath of Sithis to escort me beyond our sanctuary.nnBut that's not it, is it? Why are you here?
Hey there! Bad news, my friend. Norion is plugged tighter than an Elf with his holes melted shut.nnBut when everything's bottled up, the trick is to seal yourself inside.
I hate funerals. The best part happens before I arrive.nnBut it doesn't care. Tell me, has it found the meat?
You need to finish up that contract. The guests were giving me funny looks. You don't think it's the axe, do you?
What a terrible day. Such a tragedy. Et cetera, et cetera.
Where is that imbescile?
Yes? Is there something you need?
Gods, I need a drink. Maybe five. I can't face Norion like this.
We gave everything to defeat Nerien'eth. And were it not for the kindness of a stranger, we would be at his mercyagain. You have my thanks, friend.nnAt least the day is won.
The Scaled Court seems to have lost the will to fight. I hear we have you to thank for that. nnAll of Dragonstar is in your debt.

The hero of Skyreach! And not a moment too soon. I was this close to taking a job as a carpenter, and I hate wood. It's full of splintersand squirrels! Tree skeevers, I call them. nnSorry, I'm rambling. But at least the mine is back in business.
Now that all that business with the wild serpent is over, maybe we can get back to the real issue at hand. This town is woefully lacking a proper brewer.
So that mantikora monster was real? Huh. Maybe I should try to find the wish-granting mammoth those Nord gladiators told me about.
Aetherian light take him! I was so certain I could best Nerien'eth this time. That I had strengthened my spells.nnIf you hadn't happened by, we'd all be dead. Again.
You're a very persuasive person, you know that? You should do some public address.
Skeetees has decided to linger awhile longer. Especially now that the Scaled Court menace no longer looms like a wamasu over a nest of durzog cubs.
The Iron Orcs won't bother us again. The Dragonstar Caravan Company will make certain of that!
Hey, I know you! Wanna hear my joke again? Guaranteed to be as funny as the last time you heard it or the next one's free!
Let's not start something we'll both regret. I could use some help and you're going to want to hear what I have to say.
I am very, very, very  very drunk. But I am also very, very, very available. So  whatcha think, sweetheart? See anything you like?
The Eight be praised at your arrival! Who knows what those dogs might have done? And the one that held their leash  the Headman! Headman Cosh is out to kill me!
March forth into the streets and teach those fiends a lesson! nnLet your faith not waiver, for the gods will be with you.

There are Scaled Court in the mountains, in a cavern the Serpent cultists called "Sanctum Ophidia." I'll meet you therea group of Gazers remains, but they'll need help.nnThe Serpent means to kill us all. Man or Mer. He doesn't give a damn.

Speak to my seneschal, Little Leaf. You'll find her to the east, along the road through the northeast passage between Upper and Lower Craglorn.nnI would be eternally grateful if you make sure no harm befalls her during her mission.
Someone said the Iron Orcs won't be a problem now. Right. If you believe that, I've got a key to the Gold Tower I can sell you.
Ah! This one hates being snuck up on.

Stendarr protect you, friend. If Virmaril is the source of this darkness, then the danger is greater than I expected.nnI will seek another way inside. A way that avoids that terrible, insistent voice.
Got somethin' to say? Save it for the arena, meat.
I can't join you for this. One of us needs to return to Belkarth and prepare the city's defenses.nnYou and the Thief  avenge Kelmen and stop this mad viper. For all our sakes.
Use the portal and return to the Observatory. I will meet you there.

I knew I could count on you! The smaller creatures should pose little threat, but be warned. One of the fell beasts is of immense size. It slaughtered half of my former companions before I escaped!nnI'll follow you inside after you clear the way.
You're back! Waityou are the one I sent to that laboratory, correct? Have you been gone long?nnNo, no. It is you. I remember that look very well!
And you've returned alive! With one, two, three  all ten fingers! A bad day for spiders, a good day to be Undaunted!
Did your adventure in the Daedric prison shock you so? Why do you not take your reward?
You give Sergeant Shaghila new hope. This one is sick of these damn Daedra everywhere. You close those portals and she will feel much better.
I can train and certify blacksmiths, clothiers, and woodworkers. If that sounds like something you'd want, we can get started.
The great warrior, Titus, seeks your counsel.
Perhaps the time has come to find one last battle to fight. I'd rather face a warrior's death while I still have some sense of who I am.

The darkness that shrouds Titus's mind blocks my connection to him. But since you touched my Apex Stone, I can still communicate with you.nnYou consider Titus to be a friend. Are you ready to help him?
<There is a place to set your delivery.>
<There is a place to set your delivery.>
<There is a place to set your delivery.>
<There is a place to set your delivery.>
<There is a place to set your delivery.>
<There is a place to set your delivery.>

You must be here to learn a craft, yes? Your alliance covers my considerable fees, allowing me to impart my knowledge at no cost to you.nnIf you prove yourself, I'll certify you as competent to fulfill crafting writs.
Zantan would kiss you, but both he and you have not bathed in some time.
You've done me a great service. I had a bad feeling about this job. Never again. The Undaunted can keep their song. I never liked it, anyway.nnThat's a lie. Dammit.

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"King Emeric offers greetings! Masters of the craft await you in <<1>>! Free training for all new to their craft; certification for accomplished crafters! All at no cost to you, citizen!"
"ATTENTION: Covenant Citizens! Masters of the craft await you in <<1>>! Free training for all new to their craft; certification for accomplished crafters! All at no cost to you, citizen!"
I'll never forget what the Daedra did to meor what you did for me.
All that's left is to destroy the Sigil Stone.nnIt will take us, and any who have entered through the Oblivion Gate back to Whisper Grove. If this isn't some kind of Daedric illusion.
We're back, aren't we? Thought that was my last delve. Perhaps it still will be. I'm not sure I could do that twice.
It might not seem like it, but Hogondar is a lonely Nord.

That was it for Brittgerd! I made it back, and I am hanging up the sword for good.nnThere are pockets to Oblivion in all corners of this worldthey could be anywhere. And I am done with Oblivion. Skyrim is just a little more pleasant.
Sobabe appreciates all you have done. She thinks she is finished with adventuring. She had her fill in Oblivion. Now she will fill with delicious Moon Sugarto forget the battle and the blood.
I have dreamed of trying an Oblivion pie since I first heard about them. But now, I erect the spine of .nnI do not like this.
A bushel of us are quitting. Cowards. For a lot of them, this was their first foray. Wamasu dens and necromancer tombs are much more pleasant than Oblivion. No one believes me.
Appreciate the assist. I can tell you've done this before.
What're you doing? Get your head down before you're spotted!
You return. Are you here for the comforts of <<1>> or do you perhaps seek this one?
Are those Imperial reports you're holding? Where did you get them?
Is there something I can do for you, Undaunted?
I never thought I would see you again. Only good thing that's happened to me in weeks.
Glirion's a good sort. Just  not too friendly. Doesn't show any emotions, really. Is bloodthirst an emotion? Never mind.
These Dremora patrols in the sewers are a great concern. nnThey keep surprising our soldiers, and Sergeant Shaghila is worried that they will eventually discover our base.
General Nesh-Tan worries about Dremora patrols. They come closer to discovering this base every day.
The arena champion returns! I hear you're quite a celebrity among Daedra now.nnYet here you are gracing us with your presence in these miserable sewers. Do you have news?
I assume that Dremora has been banished back to Oblivion. Otherwise, why are you bothering me again?
My clan brother is dangerous on his own, but don't forget his thralls. They are strong when the blood thirst overcomes them.
What's that you have there? Show it to me!
Hold there, Daedric scum! One more step and I'll . Oh! It's you again. I have the best news! You go first.
Ah, you return at last. I was beginning to lose hope. Is the storm witch dead? Do you have something of mine?
It's a good thing you found Kireth. I was about to give her up for dead when she jumped into that hole.nnAnd she tells me she convinced you to find a centurion core.
Thank you for agreeing to help. Raynor's right about one thingI should have made sure I had the right equipment before coming down here.

Well done! We heard the screeches from here! No more harpy aeries. That means we can prepare for a final assault.nnSay though, Captain Skorgat stumbled in, half-conscious, muttering about an army of Briar Hearts. He was delirious, right?

How long must I abide in this gods-forsaken city? I'm freezing out here!nnNot only that, but it's starting to appear as if we will have to go kill a a group of bandits out in some old ruin they call Watcher's Hold.
Oh, hello! You see I'm doing quite well in spite of our disappointment. When life gives you guar, make guar-skin bags, so I say.
This one cares nothing about Captain Marcl's pathetic excuses. His share depended on him delivering the goods on schedule. nnHe is late, so he gets paid less. There is nothing more to say.
How have you been?
Mmm. That egg was delicious. Thank you. nnI think we also succeeded in reversing the hagraven's curse. I'd say this whole affair went very well.
Hold on. We've got one, two, three, four, and  Elvira nnSomeone's still missing though. I think. I just can't remember who it is.
I sell rare items from the Alik'r desert. Are you a collector? If not, then I fear my wares would be of little interest.
Thank you again for your help. I have sent word to my clan and they have decided to attempt contact with the Orcs in the ruin.

With the Orcs returning and building new farms, my livestock potions are in high demand.nnThe superstitious thugs in the Orsinium guard tried to shut me down, but they're fools. I told them it's just colored water and they actually believed it.
Yes, what is it?
Eggs! Beautiful, glorious eggs. They're truly a gift from the gods! nnYou can hatch them to get chickens, you can boil them, you can fry them  you can even throw them at people for fun!
Great. Can't just leave him out here. Going to have to clean this up.

Now I just have to get Captain Marck to come back to his senses, then we can get off this damned frozen beach.nnOf course, I don't know whether we should to to the Morkul clanhold first, or just straight to Orsinium .
Go! Go on! Leave medamn you! I can take care of myself!
You did that quickly, but perhaps not quickly enough. I fear the riekr may have destroyed my schematics by now. nnTell me though, you went to so much trouble. Do you at least have the antidote?
You're here and you're not dead. Not yet anyway. That's interesting. And useful, I think.
Calreth could really use that equipment. Don't wait too long to deliver it to him.
Yes, what is it?
These really are marvelously well-preserved. Though I suppose the cold must help with that.nnI will need to study them more to determine exactly when these Orcs arrived, however.
This seems like a wasted opportunity, but I'll defer to your expertise in diplomatic matters.

Well I'll be a Bosmer's arse! Outside of King Kurog, I'd say your the most famous Orc in all Tamriel. I hear you've killed more people than the Knahaten Flu! nnWhy haven't you come home to Orsinium though? Maybe you're not tough enough for Wrothgar?

So Gurgum finally found you? Took his damn time  but you're here. That's what counts. nnWelcome to Orsinium. Amazing how fast we've rebuilt, isn't it? We Orsimer can do anything when we work together.

Thank you for sparing a moment to speak with me. I fear such civility is not always common here in Orsinium, but I am working to rectify that. nnAt the crux of the problem lies our people's long-running devotion to the Daedric Prince, Malacath.

All right. I guess it's out of the bee hive and go back to the hornet's nest. nnOrsinium. My enemies there may be less mad, but they're dangerous just as well  in their own way. If you're willing, I'd like you to come with me.
What happened? Did you find Shawaz?
Outsiders may not have much sense, but some have honor.
Damn. My master works with some nasty concoctions, so I'm no stranger to bad smells, but you positively reek. Even from over here.nnWhere have you been? Crawling around in the sewers?
The now full crate sits here, waiting for you to sign the shipment manifest.
Oh. I heard footsteps and thought you might be my husband coming home at last. I hope Canuldil is all right.
Did you do it? Did you ruin the ore?
As long as those portals are active, our base is in danger of being discovered. Close them without delay.
Do you not smell the danger? Crouch and hide!
May Ruptga guide your steps, soldier. If you can't get those portals closed, we may need to move our base.
What're you doing? Get your head down before you're spotted!
I prefer the blood and sweat of a duel to the death to a test of skill, but I guess it worked out. Gloorig's going to be a fine chieftain.

Assisting with research like this is a noble pursuit. We must educate people.nnSure the riekr bathe in filth and sometimes eat their young, but these behaviors maintain their social structure. Some of their other behaviors are quite advanced.
Gloorig will make an  acceptable chieftain. He is strong and capable. The clan will prosper.
Ah, I can smell the all-too-familiar stench of Riekr on you. I'm guessing you have the items Nellic wrote me about. Good.nnWhat about Apprentice Mezhun? Any word from him?
Ruddy Elf. If I see him again I'll twist his skinny little neck off his bony little shoulders.
Have you ever had a riekr on your back and just can't get it off? The little bastard almost bit my ear off!nnSometimes you just have to know when you're beaten, and this  this is one of those times.
I'll be all right. I was just really excited about that helm. If it's cursed though, forget about it!nnI just need a few moment to compose myself. I'll be fine. Really.
How long are you going to have us standing here? Let's move!nnI want my throne room back!
The Bloody Curse has exacted its price from the heathens. You served well as the instrument of my vengeance, mortal. nnYou are strong, especially for one who isn't one of my children.

That banekin got me good in my last bout. I took down a clannfear, but that little bastard snuck up on me. Got me bleeding like a pig.nnYeah. I suspect that's going to turn out to have been my last fight.

You must be either brave or foolish to hazard these streets, but I salute you nonetheless as a fellow soldier. nnI am looking for my brother. He's about my height, a little younger  has a terrible haircut. Don't suppose you've seen him?
I heard you put on quite a show in there. They said when you threw that Ice Heart on the table the room just went completely silent.nnI wish I could've been there.
I never truly thought I would see you again, stranger. Nothing ever truly changes in this place. For the better at least.
I never truly thought I would see you again, stranger. Nothing ever truly changes in this place. For the better at least.
I never truly thought I would see you again, stranger. Nothing ever truly changes in this place. For the better at least.
Well now. Seeing you, I'm betting the situation in there's already been contained. nnWe came as soon as we heard. Is High Priestess Solgra all right?
This is precisely what I was concerned about! These bloodthirsty  Malacath-loving monsters! To just brazenly attack the Temple like this?nnWhere in the Stars was the Orsinium guard?
I'm glad I found you!
So you've agreed to help with the trials, then. An interesting twist in this strange little tale.
Damn that bitch. She put out my eye!
Well, what are you waiting for? No one's going to carry you up to the Nobles District.
Hello again, outsider. Yazara chose well. You set a hard mark to beat.
Herding tutorial
Hunt complete.
I'm sorry you had to face her alone. I read in the Scroll there would have been  consequences for me had I gotten involved in that battle.nnHad to time that portal just right.
The now full crate sits here, waiting for you to sign the shipment manifest!
You have something to tell me?
So, what have you killed lately?
When you slosh your way through that water outside, don't think about the fact that it's just a big latrine. Makes me glad I don't have to wade through it.nnWhat's on your mind?
<No new notices have been posted to the Hunting Board since you last checked.>

I cannot express what this means to me. This district is close to my heart. My family moved here from the Summerset Isles way back in the First Era.  nnWe have lived here for generations. I only hope we can remain for generations to come.

There you are. You just missed it. The ground was shaking and it felt like the entire district was about to be plunged into the abyss.nnI'm guessing that means you didn't get there in time to stop the ritual?

I was Grand Champion in the arena last year. I never had any real competition. One thing about the Daedra taking overat least it's a challenge again.nnEvery day gets a little harder. Eventually, I'll lose, but until then, I'll keep fighting.
You are a smart one, walker. Aishah can tell these things. She can appraise a person just as she can appraise the goods brought to her to sell.
Thank you for agreeing to help me. I have nowhere else to turn, and  that thing  it must die.nnI'm glad you understand.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
I TOLD YOU TO CLOSE THE MAW, BUT HERE YOU ARE, NOT IN THE TRIAL.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
Thank you for easing a mother's mind. Shining-Eyes does not like it when I treat him like one fresh-from-the-egg, but it is so cold  he should have carried his shirt with him when he went out.
By the Egg, tell me she didn't . I recognize that shirt you're carrying. My mother sent you, didn't she?nnIf my scales were not frozen, they would be purple with embarrassment.

Ah, there you are, my risk-seeking friend. Even when it's been tested before, a spell like this can be unpredictable. I'm glad you didn't get pulled into the Veil yourself.nnTell me though, did the spell work? Were you able to banish the Veilweavers?
Well, at least one of my babies is safe. Please, keep looking!
Welcome back. Did you acquire those specimens for me?
Don't dawdle. The Daedra could be on us at any moment.
I heard the bugle all the way over here. Did my archers' arrows strike true?

The heat of the rocks here is comforting in this cold climate. This one must remain here. He is watching for a ship called the Dawn Posset. It carries very important cargo.nnThe ship is many days late now, but Azaro must maintain his vigil.
Thank you for offering to look for Paratus. You have no idea what this means to me.
You are not a Daedra, are you? What do you want?
Knowledge of your enemy's movements is half the battle. The easier half, in my experience.
It's better to know what happened to my lovely wife than to spend my days wondering.nnThank you.

One thing about the city falling under attack  it may be violent and frightening for most people, but for someone who's worked every day for five years, it's actually relaxing. nnJust not having to be at that miserable place  it's liberating.
Please do hurry along. nnI hope Gryna's still in the Arboretum, but she could be anywhere by now  or worse, what if she really is dead? It's simply unthinkable.
You have my thanks friend.
You have my thanks friend.

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"King Emeric offers greetings! Masters of the craft await you in <<1>>! Free training for all new to their craft; certification for accomplished crafters! All at no cost to you, citizen!"
You have my thanks friend.
I don't care how great the Moth Priest says you are. The Palace should be reclaimed under the banner of the Empress Regent.nnDon't make a mess of this.
The Priest made us wait all this time  for you? I expected an army. I hope you know what you just signed up for, stranger.

Sister Arminus assures us you're to play a vital role, today.nnOf course, she also said that we're standing on a pinion of reality, that we have no idea how lucky we are we haven't been whisked into the cosmic beyond. And then she laughed about it.
Please find Maximinus, if you can. I desperately need that money!
You've got to prove yourself first youngblood. Just try to survive your first match and you'll advance up the ladder.nnGet inside the arena when you're ready. The crowd's getting restless.
I don't need your help. I am my own person. Other people are cimpediments to achieving total independence and success.
I've always hated spiders, but I think today proved that squashing them can be extremely gratifying.nnAt any rate, you've been a great help. Two-Blades will probably want to thank you, too.
Ah, Nesh-Tan hears that you have swum deep in blood river. I am pleased.nnYour victory in the Arena has become legend, even among the Daedra. What brings you back to this sewer base?
I dare not stay in one place for long. The Daedra are everywhere. Did General Hal-Rei send you? Speak quickly!

What have we here? It's the champion of the arena! I hear you've got quite a following among the Daedra.nnSo what in Oblivion brought you back down here? If it weren't my duty, I wouldn't be here. This place is disgusting.

If General Nedras has sent you, this one is sorry to disappoint. nnTell that cranky little elf that Pudazi still has not seen the handsome wizard. Dark moons may have cast a shadow across his path. He may be dead.
These damned portals  Shor's bones. Why can't they ever open up to someplace nice? I'd give my left thumb for a portal to Sissy Snowbeak's brew house!
Excellent! I thought you'd say that. Now remember, just survive each round and you'll advance up the ladder.nnGet inside the arena when you're ready. The crowd's getting restless.
The Rat hopes you find the arena fighters before the Daedra make them fight again. nnThey need poultices or the fights won't even be interesting to watch, and that's really what the Rat cares about.
Ezudash wishes you good luck. Clumsy walkers like you always need it, yes? Ha!
May Tava guide your steps, wayfarer. May she take you to the people of this city who are in need, and bless your efforts to help them.nnGo now. You have done all you can here.

Watch out for Covenant and Pact soldiers out there. If by some miracle, the district's already captured, blow the horn to let me know. For the gods' damn sake, no one else has. nnWhen you're done, report back here. Luck be with you, comrade.

Eyes of Akatosh! You just went out there  and just  just like that, like it was just a small matter or something. nnHere I was talking to you, and you didn't even say anything. I think that's kind of rude, isn't it?
You'll have to excuse my brother. He's a little prickly, but his heart's pure. Perhaps I can make it up to you.nnI have some information I think your alliance might find extremely valuable.
Travel down the river is not cheap.
Eyes of Magnus! All I can see is a shadowy form, you are not a Daedra, are you? I hope not. nnWhere are you, exactly? What part of the city?
The lock on this Imperial coffer has been broken and it appears someone took any valuables within but left a stack of documents.
Our funds are exhausted. You'll need to come back later.
I'd love to help you, but my hands are tied. New funds won't be available until later. You will come back later, right?nnRight?
The till is closed. You Enforcers were just too efficient today.
You'll need to hang on to that contraband just a little longer. The cupboard is bare, as they say.
Ah, Enforcer. I was so looking forward to dealing with you. Alas, you'll have to return later.
I can't accept any more confiscated goods. Come back later. I'll make it up to you. Promise.
I'm closed. Come back another time.
Sorry, my funds have run dry. Kind of like my thirst. I need another drink!
We're all out of funds. No rewards for returned contraband until later.
Another Enforcer looking for payment? Come back later. We're out of funds.
Oh dear. You'll have to come back another time. We've nothing to give you right now.
Sorry. We're, uh, low on gold right now. Come back later.
Ah, we're out of funds right now, but come back later. We'll pay you, I promise!
Don't be angry with me. It's just  we're a little low on gold right now. Come back later, please?
More contraband? A pity, we're all out of gold. But come back later, hmm?
The Guard is not currently distributing rewards. You'll have to return another time.
Glad to see you've decided to join our number. Remember: we exist to protect the weak and the innocent. That is our first and highest calling.

I sense your uncertainty. There is a darkness weighing upon your mind that only serves to deepen your despair.nnFear not. The roots of the Mundus are strong, and we are the leaves to gather the sunlight.
You succeeded recruiting one Watchman - can you succeed with another?
Who would have guessed that Julien and I would end up together? When he spoke those words, I understood what love truly is.
Maybe my time in the army will help me sort things out.
You look like a Werewolf in disguise to me, stranger.  Best keep your distance, I'm not one to be trifled with.
Did Julien and Guendeline work out?  Proud of yourself for the hand you had in that debacle?
The ambrosia flows unabated, thanks to you, friend.
You've been a constant and welcome help to our camp.  We cannot thank you enough.
Don't think you're welcome around these parts until you check in with the Warden.
Keep your distance from me. I know a Werewolf in human form when I see one!
Have you found me another villager to tort- I mean, to test?
You've news about the missing bodies? About my brother?
Very well. We're neither of us getting any younger. Get on with it.
Found something, did you? I could smell you coming.
That awful old wolf was probably magicked by those Wyrd. Thank you for killing that brute!
Thank you for helping the Hands of Northmoor. You are a light in the darkness.
Damnable Rooks. I'd pay a fair price to see them all in the grave.
You've done quite a bit for me and the cause here in King's Guard. I know finding the symbols of Arkay and getting the limbs from zombies weren't easy tasks. You have my humble thanks.
Let's begin.
Evil lurks all around us. We must burn it wherever it appears.
No even those bloody Magis Order deserve to be raised. Let's get started.
I understand helping Elsie, but Roche was hurt deep when he lost his sone. Try not to judge him too harsh.
How goes the battle?
Most people think Vandica doesn't exist.
Please hurry...I've not much time...
I've been horrible to you, and still you helped me. You're a good person.
It's time to clear the camp.
You perhaps misunderstood when I said my message was urgent. Go. Now.
The Hero of Glenumbra. No doubt you have many questions.
When you've completed your patrol, we'll speak again.
That big wolf showing up has everyone in Grayborne on edge. That's how we lost Westtry, you see - giant wolves.
Return to me when you have ensured my box works.
I see you've returned. Have you decided you believe me?
Your face looks troubled. What did you find?
I've one more thing you can do, if you are willing.
You've done a great deal to help me. If you find yourself in Wayrest, look me up, and I'll try to return the favor.
A customer is a customer, but unless you speak with Warden Godwin I won't serve you. Too many wolves in the corral already,
I'm afraid there is no change to Varic's condition. Did you find Thetis?
You helped get my friends back! I didn't think I'd see them again.
I owe you my family's life. I'll never forget you.
There's more to you than it seemed. The men who returned said it was you who guided them back.
I can protect myself. Let's just leave this wretched place.
Ah, the killer of werewolves is back! I've much to do, but hope you are well.
Eek! These flies are doing horrid things to my hair!
Oh, I hope Grit's okay!
Ah, hello. Do you have some business with the Temple of Zenithar?
No matter what it looks like, William isn't at fault. There's something eating away at his mind.nnLook around us. It's the Daedra. I don't know how we can save him, but we must.
I would never put an outsider in this position, but we are backed against a wall. Attacked by Coldun from the spirit realm and the realm of the living. These are desperate times.
We have no time to waste! Speak to Natasha so we may enter the Veil!
I am glad to see you back with us, in the land of the living. It would appear that Coldun has already caused a stir within the spirits of the Veil..
You are setting yourself up for failure in this mission.. if only the others would of known what you know...
Unless you plan to help us, I really don't have time to talk.
Every hour that draws closer to Coldun's arrival takes a part of me with it.. I do not know how we will survive.. I just do not know.
Perhaps father was right all this time.. I should have gone with him!
It is done.. We've struck a blow to Coldun that will set them back... but they will return with a force that we will not be able to stop...
You haz flowers yet? No.. no you don't! You still stinky.
Do not underestimate the Bloody Eye.
I will meet you in the northern residential district, by the footbridge. Hurry!
I'm going! I'm going!
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
I trust you were able to vanquish the wraiths?
I'm going! I'm going!
What news do you bring me?
Please let me know if I may be of further use.
So how's that goblin killing going?
Soon we will bring peace to Westtry's spirits. It will take time, but we will prevail.
My parents are at peace, thanks to you.
Did you find the gold?
You should speak with Cleric Sellan. He knows how to purge evil from places such as this.
What have you discovered?
The Duke has returned, thanks to your timely intervention. nnHe wants to see you inside.
Did my potions work? Tell me you have good news!
You're the one who "helped us out" recently, aren't you? While we can't openly discuss your actions, you have my sincere thanks.
My men don't deserve such a horrible fate. Neither do those poor souls whose bodies were stolen.
Are they here? Are Faolchu's cursed offspring here in Aldcroft?
Help us complete the spell to fuse us once more, and we will reward you.
Did you find any clues in the Mud-cloaked Hags' dens?
Have you found any Mandrake?  They're all around the swamps, particularly near the water.
Namira will never allow my spirit to find rest, but I thank you for your help.
Use the sighting gem if you need our help. Our mages can use it to focus their magic on your enemies.
Knight Adept Bieller is one of our best scouts, but he's been gone a bit too long.
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
You have done a good deed - the wailing of the ghosts grows weaker.
You've arrested Moreau, then?nnI never thought I'd live to see the day such a thing would happen here.
We must discover the reason the spriggans have risen up against us.
Our Wyrd Tree is now free, thanks to you, <<1>>, yet corruption remains throughout High Rock. Our battle has just begun.
Those feathers would be perfect for my lures!
Well met, my fellow adventurer! You are an adventurer, right?
The spirits have appeared! Quickly, <<1>>! See what you can learn about the corruption of our land.
Even now, goblins pour barrels of poison in the stream by Westtry. That river runs all the way to Aldcroft. Soon, their people will sicken like ours... unless you can stop the goblins.
Every seed is a blessing to bestow on the land.
I have to believe Tomas that got away when the soldiers came. I'm sure he's hiding somewhere. The old barn would be the most likely place.
The locket has to be in one of the houses out there. Be careful, <<1>>.
My fever breaks! I can breathe again!nnThe spirits of the land have returned to our glen.
What's this you're giving me?
You're braver than I am. I would not tread these woods alone. What have you got there?
Even in numbers, we fear to walk the paths here. What can I help you with?
You'll find goblin idols throughout the forest. Just keep an eye out for the goblins.
There's no way to know what some folks will do when times are tough, is there?
Is something wrong? You... you haven't changed your mind, have you?
Good day, traveler. Have you heard anything about my missing ring?
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
What do you want? Are you with the temple?
Not an easy decision to make, I suppose.  The times are dangerous and difficult.
Have you our new Varla Lens, Numinous?
Thank you for freeing Ameralee from that horrendous spell. Your assistance once again proves invaluable, Numinous.
Terrible creeping things... and all those eyes. Nothing should have that many eyes.
You have fought the Sload? Then my Lure functioned properly! I can use it to... attract disgusting monsters. Hmm. That function is a little narrow....
Have you exposed those stealthy Maormer yet? Use the Irradiant Jewel in the southern end of the Stonewake.
Once you have destroyed an Aquiferi Elemental, collect its Pith and bury it in a Fissure.
By Xarxes, that was quite unpleasant! Your aid was timely indeed. I am in your debt, Optimate.
Take the Starglass to the Sky-Well that lies southeast of here.
I can smell the roses from here! Please deliver them to High Priestess Vendialara at the Fan of Breath, north of here.
The storm abates, yet the clouds of ill omen linger.
By the sound of it I divine you have found us a Blessed Bell.
Return to Sunhold, and destroy the siege engines that have devastated Isque!
We are the magic and steel of the High King.
The Spellfire Pillars must be disabled.
Ah. You. How may I serve?
Have you checked on my soul gem?
The Lion Guard serves the High King, and we will not fail him.
Now you see me. Now you... well, you get the idea.
Rolantae's plan is a gamble. Had we not an immortal Numinous to aid us, I would not even consider it.
Foxglove nectar? Is that what she said? That would speed those poor soldiers to their doom. Wolfsbane is what they need!
Wolfsbane is the bane of wolves, but werewolves are hardly wolves, are they? Hm. Are they?
Praise the Stars, our Varla Lens is safe once again. You have done well, Numinous.
I just can't raise my blade against Coren, even knowing he's not really in there. I'm trusting you to help us both.
Take care, Numinous! You must place each Crown Piece on the Channeling Pedestals at exactly the right time .
Check the Pearls to the south to ensure Optimate Illira isn't contemplating the gravest sin...
Bless you, friend. Not many would risk themselves to honor the family of another.nnMy father would have liked you.
I'm not crazy. I swear to you I'm not. Follow the orphans. You'll see.
Your fingers were deft and subtle upon the Sacred Instrument. I believe I shall regret that your calling lies not within my temple.
Auri-El returns at last! Your deeds shall be recorded in the annals of our history evermore.
With the Greater Welkynd Stone which powered Auri-El, our Vartisans may be able to restore the fallen planet back to its rightful place.
The divination must begin immediately after you have infused the Welkyn Stone. Are you prepared?
Hurry to Vilmo. He waits for you at the Mage's Shrine.
I sense you bring dark tidings....
You'll see an old set of ruins west of here. Follow the cliffs down, and you'll find the island where Ulorion called out to the spirits years ago.
This cannot be true. It was only a book....
The fate of Glenumbra may hinge on your upcoming battle. Fight well!
The Varla Lens has been stolen? And you are tracking the thief? Well what are you doing here?!
We have failed to kill the Stormwitch. Shall we try again?
Is it done? Are my friends at peace?
I see in your eyes that you bring bad news. Tell me what you learned about my son.
Panoit's a good leader. I trained him. If there's a way to make that thing work again, he'll find it.
I suppose I will eventually gather more rats. Still, what a bother!
I believe I shall take a brief sabbatical from teaching. I feel a distinct need to... stretch my legs.
Why do you stand here? Seek not my company, but that of Battlereeve Artulion. He awaits you at the beach west of Dusk.
Thank you for rescuing the survivors, <<1>>.
Al'kari's chickens will never sing again. Al'kari suffers great pain. Leave Al'kari alone.
You're... different. You're a better person than most of the traveller I meet. nnFew would concern themselves with the day-to-day problems of a small place like Crosswych. nnI wish you luck, friend.
The Gem Spider situation is quite under control now. I highly recommend you visit the enclosure, to observe the fruit of your labors.
With the information you've provided about the Red Rook bandits, I think we can get King Casimir to send more troops.
<<1>>, you did it!
No time to waste. Take care out there, <<1>>
Praise to you, Numinous! I can feel that the Ascendants have been freed!
Bless you for helping us - I know it seems like a mundane task, but you'll help me save the lives of many injured miners.
Ahh... Our dear, celebrated Numinous. So good of you to join me.
So you found the Great Elum, after all. A shame it couldn't be saved - even so, we must worry about human lives.
For you, I may be able to offer a special price.
Browse my wares. You will not find their like again, I think.
I shall never forget the sight of the Varla Lens rising once again over our Kinhouse.
Have you brought the Dawnshards? They can be found within the Nodules scattered along the eastern ridge of the Stonewake - opposite us.
In times of peace, there would be dozens of young sculptors here to learn. Instead, we train soldiers.
By restoring the Varline, you have eased my mother's fevered thoughts. I thank you, Optimate.
My work is fulfilling in many ways, yet I long to create something that will spread my renown throughout Tamriel.
Thanks for finding my pickaxe, friend.
I have inspected the horn.
Maormer infiltrators may be anywhere. Be cautious.
State your name and status. Necessities impend.
A new Emissary has arrived from High Kinlady Astraea's domain. He tells me the Kinlady was extremely grateful for your work.
Ahh, at last. I breath the fresh air. In and out, in, and out. How marvelous!
By the Et'ada! Without your aid I surely would have fallen to those Maormer devils. For that, you have my thanks. Please continue on to the Kinhouse; Kinlady Genivra awaits.
Truly magnificent! The damage you wrought on the Maormer supplies must surely burn in their minds... and bellies!
The Maormer are far from their fields and homes. That is their weakness.
Vigilance keeps the Pallid Devils at bay.
The Pallid Devils' bombardments have finally ceased!
You do not appear injured. Is this important?
I beg you, show mercy. Roberte and I will make this up to Thierry. I can't lose him.
I beg you, spare Roberte. He's a good man. He just made a bad choice.
Oh my. It appears I have forgotten to put on my bodice again.nnDid you need something?
I am bored. You! Dance! Dance faster!
Have you tried the device yet? Which way did the thief go?
Praise to you, Optimate. Report thy deeds to Battereeve Tariella. She will be pleased by our success here today.
Praise to you, Optimate. Report thy deeds to Battereeve Tariella. She will be pleased by our success here today.
Praise to you, Optimate. Report thy deeds to Battereeve Tariella. She will be pleased by our success here today.
Praise to you, Optimate. Report thy deeds to Battereeve Tariella. She will be pleased by our success here today.
You will find Prodigious Mudcrabs in and around the waters to the north of here.
Shall you save us from the Maormer?
An auspicious welcome to you, Optimate. It is unfortunate you come to us amidst another foolish invasion, but I am certain the Maormer will falter soon.
An auspicious welcome to you, Optimate. It is unfortunate you come to us amidst another foolish invasion, but I am certain the Maormer will falter soon.
The Metalwrights demand precision in every aspect of life - not just metalworking.
Is it true what the apprentices say? Auri-El shall be returned to the sky, and it is all thanks to you. Numinous... I misjudged thee. You are a hero indeed.
With Orgnavar gone I am once again able to focus on the divine bodies. Praise to you, Optimate.
Praise and honor to you, Optimate!
What business do you have here?
I should thank you for your level head in this matter.
The winds from the Fane carry your name in honor, Optimate.
I'll get the letter to King Faharajad. You'd best return to Lakana.
<<1>>, you're my only hope. nnYou and Maelys will find Invold, won't you? You'll find a way to set me free. nnMay the Eight guide you... and help us all.
I am charged with the defense of this Kinhall. Ever do the Maormer send forth their odious zombies.

My superior sent me here to die. nnI know she did, or I would have seen more Lion Guard soldiers patrolling this road.nnBefore I die, I want to save Dabienne Vanne. Have you learned anything that will free her?
Please. Please hurry. I'm afraid. What if it's too late?
Did you find a coven member? Did they tell you what we needed?
I can't believe my mistress is gone!nnWhat kind of heartless monster could do such a thing?

Ah, here you are. We've received some disturbing reports about Lord Montclair's captives.  A sickness called the blood fever is spreading amoung them. They say it drives a man to madness.nnNo doubt this is Montclair's work. He's already mad!
Have you heard any news about my men? nnPlease, find them. I can't return home without news of their whereabouts.
What have I done? What have I done? I thought I could kill the bastard, but instead he  he turned me into a  a monster!
I would see every one of the soldiers under his command exiled, but there is only one just punishment for those who betrayed me. That is death.nnTell me you've spilled their blood.
You could not wake him? I feared as much. He has fallen into an impossible sleep, one from which I fear he may never wake.
Look for Gregor at the inn. He's a thirsty one.
If there was an organized plot against the duchess, none of my spies got wind of it. nnEven the best security can do little to stop a single, determined madman.
I think Duke Nathaniel might have done it. nnFor some time, I've wondered if such political marriages are doomed from the start.
If our historian was here, she could write the tale of Shornhelm's recent troubles much better than my scrawled ramblings.nnIt's a pity that she and so many others are gone.

This rescue was just the beginning. Now it's time for our crippling strike.nnOne of the fleeing slaves spotted Montclair headed into the cave at the rear of the mews. He has yet to emerge. nnThis is our chance!
Have you completed your task?
Belene Ancois is an uppity woman. Serves her right to be married to a chicken farmer now.nnWhy she wants to continue her father's provisioning business is beyond me. Maybe she's really a spy.
You found it! That's wonderful! You can save Aunt Dabienne.nnUm... don't show my diary to my father. He wouldn't understand it.
End my pain. Release me from my torment.nnThat dagger will be sharp and true against someone as cursed as me.
You must drain three anchoring Soul Gems. Once depleted, the power of each gem will be yours.nnWhen the last anchor drops, I'll try to flee. nnIf I make it, I'll meet you back at Fell's Run.
Any stranger in Alcaire should be careful. We don't tolerate crime.
The people of Koeglin Village were not always like this. I fear for Ganise. She is filled with such jealously and grief.
We wouldn't have survived without your help. Thank you.
I can feel it: the mayor still has a task you must complete.nnHelp her find some peace. Then she can lead us again against the abomination.
I'll make sure none of the infected get out from here. Keep on your guard, and stay safe. I don't trust anyone here, not even that Verandis fellow.

Thank you for aiding in our cause. When you find knights in the keep who would stand up for what's right, send them to me out here. nnWe will make preparations to storm the keep and stop Sir Croix and this rash attack.
We're hanging on by a thread here. If we can get a few more soldiers to reinforce us, I'll feel much more secure.nnIf we're lucky, Moira's Hope will have people to spare.
Testing greeting text for problems.
I'm still getting the hang of this feeding thing. But don't worry. We only feed on willing vassals or evil villains. And we never feed to excessexcept maybe on the evil villains.
What a glorious spectacle! You were unstoppable!
Today, we drink, for tomorrow, we die! Ha! What do you think of that, friend?
I hope the infusion restores Makana's memory. He need only inhale it and it will heal him.

I fear that with the fervor afflicting Menevia, the Moonbird has been hurt or killed. S'rashi deals in all information expensive and exotic. If anyone has heard rumors of the Moonbird, it will be him.
You must have had some success. It's quieter here already!nnThose poor souls must have suffered much, but their wailing has caused enough trouble here.
They are going to release me, aren't they? Has Olivier really not come forward? nnHe will. I know he will.
Forgive me for my earlier outburst. I must have made quite a fool of myself.nnPlease, forget everything I told you.

You've returned. I assume this means you don't believe I'm a ruthless killer. Perhaps you've come to avenge the many people I've slain.nnNo matter. What's done is done, and I can never hope to atone for it.
If you can get me out of this cage, I can reach the surface on my own.
You poured the packets into the braziers and nothing happened? That's it then. We have no choice but to surrender.nnGo tell the king. I'll be down here. Praying that he sees reason.
You return, and sooner than S'rashi expected! nnYou have S'rashi's gold? Please say you have S'rashi's gold.
You can come and go as you like.nnThough you're a fool if you don't just go.
You've got a free pass to go in or out. nnIf I were you, I'd pick out.
I'm certain you and my husband have much to discuss. nnDon't worry. As soon as you're done, we'll play another game.
My men have moved the Moonbird's cage to the pool behind my estate. It is now yours - retrieve it whenever you wish.
Heard you got those stingy horsemen to part with a few steeds. I can't thank you enough!
We have little time to strike. We must succeed, or all is lost.
I'm so tired.nnIt would be so easy to just sleep.
Oh, praise the Eight it's you! Quick! Untie me!
My pickaxe. Over there. You must help me complete the offering.nnWithout the offering, we are lost. Lost in our nightmares! Lost forever!

You'll find House Tamrith in the western district of Shornhelm and House Dorell to the east. nnBe warned: The two houses are at each other's throats, even in times like these. Before they'll hear you out, you might have to side with one or the other.
Please hurry! I don't know how much longer Charlotte can hold on.
I've been banned from selling my wares in this camp. I think I've overstayed my welcome. Perhaps we'll meet another time, friend.
Do you have it? Quickly! I think she's getting worse!
The Omen of Counting stars is not visible to those who are awake.nnYou must confront it within its own realm.

Go through the northern district. The <<1>> is entered through a tunnel near Lord Montclair's manse.nnI'll meet you at the entrance later after you've rescued the captives  or perhaps I should say, "If you rescue the captives ."
We meet again. I have seen many horrors since we last spoke.nnLady Eselde asked me not to come, but I could not let my visions come to pass. The <<1>> must be destroyed!
I am glad we don't have to worry about those filthy ogres anymore. That sure makes my life easier.
What news from the Imperial palisade?
You should have no trouble finding Moondrop Mold - look for the glowing bits of fungus about the swamp.
Watch yourself in the Man-Grove. Wood Orcs are always hungry for a weary traveler.

Looking to become the Grand Gladiator? You're like so many others.nnFight in the arenas below us. Each victory will earn you a Hammerdeath Victory Token. nnI look forward to watching you kill. Don't disappoint me.
I couldn't care less what your problem is. nnIf you touch Lord Moric, I'll show you what your intestines look like.
The crowd has gathered. The bets are placed. nnAre you ready to face Grul the Destroyer, or will you run away with your tail between your legs?

They say I'm mad, you know. Apparently my emanation theory makes me crazy, but mages who make deals with psychotic murdering creatures from endless realms of fire and ash? They're perfectly sane.nnBah! We'll see who's mad.
What in Oblivion's name happened in there? Heloise ran right past me, crying her eyes out. nnWell, don't just stand there! Get after her! She's not safe out there on her own.
Urgh!
As deep creak rumbles up from within the Swamp Cypress.
A wrinkle in the bark of the tree curls at you, as if in a smile.
I don't suppose you'd be up for burial detail, would you?nnThere's more to a war than fighting, after all.nnAlways more work to do.
In life, I failed to save these people. Thank you for saving them in death.
Did you gather those thumbs yet?

How Tamrith can stand that Zeli woman is beyond me. She prays day and night! It's really annoying. nnI hope she knows how to use a weapon when the time comes. Baron Dorell will order us to attack sooner rather than later, I think.
An Infernal Device of sload legend! Arkay blessed us when you arrived.nnAnd look, Aldmeri reinforcements arrived!

You must be very brave or very foolish to follow in our footsteps.nnIt's a pity you found us this way, waiting about like lambs for the slaughter. We will not fall without taking the whole of this accursed place with us!
Is that Saproot I smell?
I will rest peacefully knowing you have saved Razorvine. nnPlease, take this to Priestess Fleile at the refuge to the north.nnTell her of your success. She will be pleased.

Use the torch and burn poor Gennove's body. If bloodfiends are really involved, we can't take any chances.nnBut make sure you collect his ashes. It wasn't his fault he died like that. He deserves to be buried in hallowed ground.
The Swamp Cypress seems to point to the Mound of Dirt to the east.
Sir Edmund will stay on as leader of the Knights of the Flame. He is a good man, and loyal. Though I fear I will never trust anyone fully again.
Bury those body parts and things should begin to return to normal around here.nnBut be carefulI think I know which graves she stole those remains from.
I have no idea how those disgusting things got into my backpack. Not a clue.
Oh, no. I recognize that staff...
Preparing the entire order to go to war isn't easy. This is going to take some time.
Roublerub's probably drunk at the Mossy Hole Tavern. That's in the Jolly Squalor.

If Ayarynne places her trust in you, so do I. The Camoran throne is rightfully mine, yet everywhere I find loyalties divided.nnI need to find those who would support me. Be my voice in this city. Speak with the Treethanes; convince them of our cause.
The proud hunters roam as rabid dogs. The pups must return to their hunt, not scavenge like crows.nnThis should not have come to pass, but you have helped right this wrong.
My nephew and I owe you our freedom. We won't forget. I grieve for Christophe, but I know you did all you could. Now, I must find my brother.
Thank you for giving me back my memory. If only Rin and I had gone to Ahtah in the first place, Christophe might still be alive.
I'm finishing up here and then heading back to the hideout. nnIf you're up for a little adventure, though, I might have something for you.
Any moment now, Shadowhiskers will unveil his master plan. They will not even see it coming.
It is <<1>>, correct? You dealt a severe blow to the Imperials in Southpoint.nnWhat have you brought me?
"Shadowhiskers." Funny name for a Khajiit, now that I think on it.
Without my cattle, I would be ruined. nnYou don't know how much you've helped me.
Thank you for healing me, <<1>>. nnI'll tell others of your kindness.
I hear King Fahara'jad's been plotting to take over Alcaire for years.
I'm glad you took care of our bandit problem. There's no room in this town for troublemakers. nnNow if we could just get Fell's Run to look past our differences and come together as a community .
Normar has high hopes for his proclamation.nnI shall remain cautiously optimistic.
Normar better resolve this situation soon.nnHis lack of action is simply unacceptable.
I presume the Queen has informed you of this cultist threat?
Fell's Run seems a good enough place to settle as any.
Destroying the Imperial tunnels was a crushing blow to their invasion. Well done!
Our deal is done. I would not linger long in my realm, unless you wish to live in your nightmares... forever.
We have little time to strike. We must succeed, or all is lost.
I know what I must do to win her heart. It's dangerous, but I think it will work.
Tristan ran off rather suddenly, didn't he? nnI wonder what's caught his interest so much?nnWhy'd he just take off like that?
Your feet move swiftly. The blessings of the Herd Mother must be upon you, friend of the Horsemen.
Thank you for your help with my supplies. You're always welcome here, and you're always a friend to Trader Nathalie.
With the dam defended we must take the fight to the ogre camp.

Good riddance to them. These poor misguided fools have enough problems keeping their heads out of the clouds without some young bit of fluff distracting them.nnYou'd best check with one of the families in Fell's Run to ensure they made it back.
I worry for our kin back in Malabar Tor.
Elladrel lives in Leaftower, which lies to the north. She can introduce you to other loyalists.nnI wish you luck reaching her. Leaftower is occupied by the Imperials.
Is the deed done, <<1>>?
A map?
And still we sit, waiting. nnAny news, <<1>>?
The herd will grow strong again, now that the weak are not holding them back. Now to find another farmhand...
Have you come to pay your respects? That's very kind of you.nnMathias was such  he was good to me. Better than I deserved, I think.
I appreciate what you've done for me. This bracelet is the only memento of my mother I have left.nnI'lll be sure it never leaves my wrist again.
Just do what you can to calm Duzug down.nnIf this goes on much longer, I may need to find a new place to raise my herd.
If it were up to me, the Ebonheart Pact would be gone from Northpoint already!

You've convinced her to continue fighting this sickness that battles her from within. For this I am thankful.nnI don't know what was spoken of, but we both put our trust in you. Whatever happens, happens. I'll be at her side regardless.
Elise and I were never close. She's so headstrong, just like her mother. She took care of her brother after my wife left.nnHow can vengeance be greater than family?
Everyone's flinging accusations, but it's plain to see.nnThe Bretons are robbing us blind!
Everyone's flinging accusations, but it's plain to see.nnThe Orcs are robbing us blind!
Foul magic has enthralled the giants. This is grave news indeed.
Montclair's trickery is more cunning each day, but he's not clever enough to fool us.nnIf he hopes to lure the Ravenwatch out with mind games, he's in for a big surprise.
What has happened to Godrun? He has become quite oppressive lately.
Slouchbears are kept behind this palisade.nnFeed them fungi. Free their minds!
Montclair's trickery grows more clever each day. It's not enough.nnIf he wants to destroy the Ravenwatch with mind games, he's in for a big surprise.
Sorcassil was summoning Molag Bal!
The pain  I won't last much longer.nnThank you for preserving the honor of the Lion Guard.
You cannot understand how my children's madness wounds me. The proud hunters roam like rabid dogs. This should not have come to pass.
I watched the harpies make off with some of our feed grain.nnThat grain is for our horses, not those flying hags!
You go on. I'll follow as soon as I catch my breath.nnGo! House Dorrell needs you. Shornhelm needs you.
The Baron has been in politics far longer than our fair Duchess. He knows when to fight and when to parley.
I'm sorry, I don't have time for an audience presently. I'm waiting for more of my friends to arrive. nnPerhaps you've seen them? I believe one of them is wearing an insignia ring of mine.
Bloodfiends and their ilk are everywhere. Finding hearts shouldn't be a problem. Collecting them might be.nnOnce you have enough, light the beacon on the far side of the canyon, across the bridge.
Whatever you decide, I will understand.
Wh-who are you? Are you a bloodfiend?nnI'm armed!
Perhaps I have misjudged your character, <<1>>. nnI don't make mistakes when leaking information.
Thank you again for returning the Pride of Northpoint safely to me. nnI'll keep them safely stored away within our treasury.
We have but one more task in front of us - restoring the Lens to its rightful place above the Kinhouse.
I cannot believe Hainen changed his student to stone. Mistress Ameralee is a far better tutor than he!
Ameralee's appearance is much improved by the blush of life.
My friend, I hope it was as fun for you to do as it was for us watching younnI thought that big one almost had you!
I hope it was as fun for you to do as it was for us to watch! nnI thought that big one almost had you!
Oh good! Seems you've placed them all back on the bookshelves.
I can't believe you found my ring.  It is priceless to me and I have been beside myself with worry.
I wish I could stop to chat, but if I stop working, we'll fall even further behind.nnDefenses can't build themselves, you know.
You were brave for confronting that demon - Isrisa would thank you could she speak.
Impressive. Your bones mended and there is no decay. Before I return the divine voice, you must decide who receives it.
Mudcrabs are delicious when boiled with simple root vegetables. I know how to cook them. I just can't catch them.
Heard you got those stingy horsemen to part with a few steeds. Can't thank you enough!
You'll find those webs and anyone they entrap all through the valley. Be careful.
Stendarr's blessings upon you.
Get back to the fight, Lieutenant! We will win this day, one way or another.
We should proceed east <<1>>, to woo the musicians of Isque.nnGo on ahead; I shall meet you at the Maldarawo's Kinhouse.
Did you get that poison from the Red Rook bandits?
Stupid horse. Does not even know how to do what he is told. I have a good mind just to feed the stupid thing to the dogs.
The Varla Lens has been stolen? And you are tracking the thief? Well what are you doing here?!
Leave me be. I have nothing to say to anyone.
Can't a soul just sit and grieve in peace?
Why are you bothering me? I have better things to do.
Do we have anything to talk about? Really, I have better things to do.
Perhaps, when it's safer, I'll move closer to Camlorn and see how I can help them.

I do not believe we have gained the loyalty of Varyllis yet, have we? It will be quite a journey back west. I recommend a pause for personal refreshment before setting out.nnYou go ahead of me, I shall meet you within the Felballin Kinhouse.
I do not believe we have aided the Varyllis yet, have we? Perhaps we should resolve that matter before pressing farther east?nnIf you go ahead of me, I can meet you in the Felballin Kinhouse.
I do not believe we have aided the Varyllis yet, have we? Perhaps we should resolve that matter before pressing farther east?nnIf you go ahead of me, I can meet you in the Felballin Kinhouse.
I lost my young wife in the confusion. I pray to Mara she fled elsewhere... or she died.nnI would not wish her in the hands of the Maormer. She is.... She would not be chained to an oar.
I must warn you our Gem Spider collection has become rather... unmanageable. The Head Keeper is nearly worn to pieces with worry.

Once your task is complete, Sabastian will meet you at the entrance to the pits  nnBe swift in your duties, and surely, the citizens of Shornhelm will sing the praises of House Tamrith. You bring us glory.
Do you have news of the Bloodsworn?
Plenty of room in the stables, if you need a place for your steed. nnAs long as he doesn't mind a few chickens scuttling about, that is.
I must warn you our Gem Spider collection has become rather... unmanageable. The Head Keeper is nearly worn to pieces with worry.
Can't trust anyone these days. We have to be careful!
What did Irne decide? Will he drop his accusations against Govran?
I am glad the River Dreugh have been dealt with. I only hope they do not return in as great a number.
That key's the most valuable piece of silver I've ever seen.nnQuick! Get me out of here!
They talk about me behind my back. I know they do.
Look for the Lion Guard scout on the road to Steelheart Moorings.nnHe seemed eager for a fight. I worry he may have taken on more than he can handle.
Now to finish the necklace - oh, I hope she likes it.
I knew I could count on those two to help us! And you, of course.nnI'm sure Colane will let us unload our cargo, and Belene will send aboard fresh supplies soon enough.
Used to be a salvager, till I hired on the Midnight Swell.
No matter who stands against us, we will protect Sir Edmund from all who would hurt him.
They say you saved us, <<1>>. I'm grateful that you came to us in our hour of need.
Forgive me for being so rude, <<1>>. nnYou should know that we're under enormous pressure.
I find I'm more comfortable among Redguards these days.nnSomething's happened to the Bretons. Something's... not quite right.
The past few months seem like a dream now. I do not know what fears haunted us, but I am glad they are gone now.
Please, kind <<1>>, help me escape these cruel slavers.
Forgive me for being so rude, <<1>>. nnYou should know that we're under enormous pressure.
If I could wield a weapon I'd be on the front line.
The Imperials brought the war to Southpoint, a poorly defended trading port...

I'll make sure Qi'Ravin is given a warrior's burial, as he deserves.nnYou must get to Farah and save her. nnThe general will be ready. He will not fall as easily as his men. He's probably positioned in the most interior of the palisades.
My family's always sold provisons to ships. Colane Oscent had no business stopping me.nnI'm glad to be rid of those chickens, even though my husband doesn't see it that way.

Check the farmlands for any signs of my wife.nnWatch your step, though. Those creatures out there... they'll stare at you with those blank eyes and innocent faces, but it's a lie! nnIt's just a disguise. They lure you in, and then they strike!
Catae's ship sank in the channel mouth to the west. J'Hriss is looking right at it.
Back already? Did you find anything?nnIf my father weren't so frightened, he'd help you, you know. He's not himself. Not since... well, not for a while.
I haven't seen any of the sailors disembark from the ship yet. Why aren't they letting them go?nnThey don't have a plague or something, do they? I was on that ship! What if they infected me, too?
Have you retrieved the head of that marsh-snake Argonian? nnEven now he terrorizes the sick and feeble!nnI suspect he actually orchestrated the outbreak, but I have yet to discover definitive proof.
No one shall shed a tear at Bravosi's passing. I pray that the Tribunal will judge his methods harshly, for he has done naught but tear our city asunder.
Please - I have no time to converse.
Blight's the obvious answer to why we haven't heard back from Fort Arand, but we don't need the risk of going.  You, we don't care about.
Imperial invaders. Altmer queens. Who thinks of the eelmer, I ask you?
Please make your visit to the Hortator brief. nnHis spirit did not die a peaceful death. He still needs some time to recover.
Even my Champion could not get through the overrun fort, yet here you stand.  Are the nests destroyed?
My death was no accident, <<1>>. nnI was murdered.nnNow I have no doubt it was through the machinations of House Dres.
We caught them by surprise and I think we have the upper hand. nnI've been wounded, though. I don't think I'd be of any more use in the battle.
The keep, the Redguards, the duchess all of this caused by Sir Hughes's madness. nnSo many have died.
You can find the Penitents all around the Conclave, seeking what we cannot give them and troubling our Clan.  When you have dealt with them, speak to my Champion.
Glad to see someone around here knows how to get things done. Now, what did you wish to speak about?
Have you found all the items Sera Orvona has requested?
You return, stained with blood. This is a good omen.
You know, if you swam to the bottom of the ocean and started digging you'd fall out of the sky.
A whole village of Black Sap, and right on our doorstep! They can't be up to any good.
What a marvelous day. It's all thanks to you, my friend! nnEat, drink, and be merry!
Your generosity knows no bounds, my darling little plaything. Rest assured, a lady keeps her bargains.
Back off, I got to this one first!
Hunt down the Band of The Three and their risen minions. nnDefeat them and their souls will be bound to my holy blade. Then we can destroy them.
Hammerdeath Arena is not far from here, but it's so much nicer to stay in the hot springs. nnI'd rather visit my friends than go all that way to place my bets... or pay my debts, it it comes to that.
I'm eagerly awaiting whatever else Lord Ra'ud has in mind for us. Anticipation is the most pleasing part of any romance.
Great news! Moments ago, the missing Jaqspur wandered out of the Thrambles. nnThey're weary, but unharmed.
Dead bears, dead men. Creatures of the Valenwood will eat well tonight!
Have we met before? No? Then come join us for a little while.
Dancing is rewarding, not just for relaxation, but also for its beguiling influence on attractive courtiers.

Adventuring and fighting monsters must get tiring. nnIf you ever want to take a break from your life of excitement, I could use a hand down here.nnI could use your help looking after this... uh... quiet barrow.
We will do all we can to halt the lamia advance. I just hope it is enough.
Continue to fight with honor, my friend. nnAnnihilate your enemies. nnEnjoy the thrill of every battle won.
I wonder what my dad was doing up there? nnDo you think he's trying to poison me?nnYou can't trust anyone these days, can you?
Trade will avoid this port now. Southpoint used to be a forgettable town, now it is forgotten.
Trade will avoid this port now. Southpoint used to be a forgettable town, now it is forgotten.
If only we hadn't finished the wine so quickly! nnI fear to stand up, lest I fall into the mud again.nnMaybe someone should... catch me.
I'll soon finish an epic love-song for my beloved. nnWhenever I start writing, though, the name of my beloved changes....
Now that they're dead... I don't know what to do with myself.nnMaybe I'll take up piracy. Do you know any good pirates?
Tell me you managed to discover what was in those packages. nnI've heard whispers on the wind of what they might contain.nnI doubt I'm prepared for the truth.
There are <<1>>s growing all over these vines. Just watch out for the bugs. And the Imperials.
Wondering what <<1>> found.nnHoping <<1>> succeeded!nnThe sensation of pleasurable suspense! The tingle of anticipation!
She's looking this way! Oh! My heart is aflutter! nnI'm about to burst with desire for Lady Diane. nnShe accepted the bouquet? What did she say? Tell me!
The view is much better from below. Go down and look! It will be glorious!
I assume the Foreman only confirmed what I told you.  If you were able to befriend him, the best thing to do is get in House Dres' trust and find out more.
I came here for peace, serenity, and free wine. nnIt's such a shame that we're out of wine.
It seems more peaceful around the Conclave. Have you been dealing with the penitents?
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
I will be the champion. No one will best me!
Hoom is playing a dirty trick on Wud. Hoom is eager to watch when he finds the lightning ants!
Enjoying your company!nnInviting you to sit with Wud.nnThe delight of friends laughing. The dismissal of woes.
Imperial invaders, Camoran rebels... and now ungodly monsters. It feels like there's no place safe in Grahtwood anymore.

You know what I miss? My bed. Clean straw and a goose-down pillow.nnSome filthy Imperial soldier's probably bedding a Bosmer harlot in it even as I speak. I shall have to have it burned when I get back.
Let's get you into your new armor.
I knew the moment I saw you, you'd put on a great show!
The sooner that wretched boy is back with his mother, the sooner we can get home.
There are rumors running around that Haven was overrun by sload necromancers.nnI should see what kind of maggots grow in the undead.
Haven't been sleeping well at all since we came ashore. Keep looking over my shoulder, too. This place is bad luck.
Haven't been sleeping well at all since we came ashore. Keep looking over my shoulder, too. This place is bad luck.
Little baby thunderbugs everywhere! Aren't they sweet?nnI can't wait to eat them!
And so it seems the plot thickens.  I'm most interested to know who spoke to you.
We have opened our village to the Colovian refugees from Haven.nnI wish they showed more gratitude.
Duke Bealton may have been a bastard who sold out his own home, but it was Baron Gradwyn's men who started the fight. A pox on both of their houses.
Duke Bealton may have been a bastard who sold out his own home, but it was Baron Gradwyn's men who started the fight. A pox on both of their houses.
Duke Bealton may have been a bastard who sold out his own home, but it was Baron Gradwyn's men who started the fight. A pox on both of their houses.
Duke Bealton may have been a bastard who sold out his own home, but it was Baron Gradwyn's men who started the fight. A pox on both of their houses.
Keep your head down out here, <<1>>.

The artisans have been working on the only two houses we have left.nnBetween the Orlishkaarn raid and sudden lava flows, they haven't been able to finish them.nnI hope the supplies you brought will allow them to fix that.
Thank you for all you've done. Once I've caught my breath, I must return to the Wyrd.
I thought we were saved when Senie's ashes spared my farm.nnLittle did I know that another disaster would take its place.
I sense unease coming from the wharf. nnI can only assume it means you've returned with good news.nnI see Irano isn't with you. Did he resist arrest?
