The Commander and I were just discussing his people.nnCommander, you know they can't just leave once we defeat them. No, they'll have to repay Valenwood. They'll all be chopped up and buried under saplings. They'll all feed the trees.nnWhat an honor!
Place the essence in the ceremonial basin. nnIts magicka will strengthen the power of the ceremony.
All this woodsy plant magic... trees aren't supposed to grow like that!
All this woodsy plant magic... trees aren't supposed to grow like that!
I've never had another woman, not after Lea. I never will. If we couldn't be together in life, then perhaps we will soon enough.nnWe'll be together in Aetherius.
Looks like that tower of bones in Haven was knocked down.nnI have to wonder. How big a pile of bones do you think that left?
I think it's time we sent raiding parties out to harass the Imperial lines. We can shoot them from the treetops!
This is a peaceful place. I wish I'd visited before the Imperial invasion.
If you venture near the docks, watch for pickpockets and petty thieves.
Still not ready to take your journeyman test <<1>>? You need to master more recipes.nnLucky I have some for sale.
Well finally, you are qualified to take your journeyman test. nnAre you ready?

I'm very proud of you, apprentice. Seldom do I get the chance to work with someone so talented and fire-resistant.nnYou need to do a little more work before I can consider you a journeyman. I have some recipes. Purchase them, learn them, craft them.
Thank you for telling me. I know it was hard to say.
Ah, <<1>> it's good to see you again.  How goes things with House Dres?
Welcome to my home. nnCome freely. Go safely.
I hope Goval can make a diagnosis from those samples.
I said, "Get out!" You're no longer welcome here.
Reme's left us? But why? My cold is coming back!
Please, let Raijo be. nnNow is not the time for talking.
I heard you were out at the weak section, doing some excellent work.  Or so my cowardly workers told me.  That part is dangerous - I can barely get them to go near it.
What bones have you brought for us?  You have the smell of the grave on you, <<1>>.
Let us keep our activities to ourselves, friend.
The <<1>> comes back.nnThe <<1>> proves useful.nnSlaughters the violaters.nnYou must stay with Mother.
Thank you, <<1>>.nnWith your help, my revenge will be complete.nnThen I can finally pass on to Aetherius.
What can I do for you, friend?nnI have yet to send these remains to the Mages Guild, but the courier should be returning soon. nnI can hardly wait to hear what these poor souls have to say!
Hero of the Summit! Hero!
To wonder at the habits of Elves and humanfolk. The savagery of their conflicts! Their failure to groom their fur!
To be most displeased and disappointed. The indignity of the circus! The bereavement of my heart!
Ah, I must be dying! All I see is white... no wait! Red!
Greetings once again, <<1>>.  A pleasure as always to see a loyal friend of House Dres.
Angof will regret what he did here. His attempt to destroy the Wyrd Tree has made us stronger than ever before.
Go watch the show, meat. You could get hurt back here.
Our craft is not without its drawbacks, yet I would have no other life.
I know. I know!
The goblins will rue the day they trespassed in our sacred forest.
You understand and respect the forest. Ghost and I are proud to call you friend.
Claire's spirit no longer responds to your hails.
Leave me, stranger. I must... gather my thoughts before I return to Mournhold. What a foul fate I must suffer!
Do you hesitate? What for? My terms are clear - kill him now.
That Prince Aeradan... what a fellow! I wonder if he knows what I'm thinking right now?
Leave this one be! I must continue to examine these samples more thoroughly. That one must let the guard at Fort Thendr know of this discovery.
That looks like a heavy load.nnYou can pile the rubble on top of the broken area of the wall behind me.

You dear, kind soul, healing my Senche out of the kindness of your heart. A thousand thanks to you!nnNow. About that Prince. I know what he wants. If he seeks to drive the Imperials out from our wood, then I am with him. I give my word.
I guarantee my information will help turn the tide of this war for your... I mean our Queen!
I'm in your debt for your assistance.nnPerhaps when this madness is behind us, I'll be able to return the favor.
By the Merciful Hand of Boethiah! You're still alive!nnThat's good, right? All we can really say around our evening fires is that we've survived another day.
Who would dare give this information so freely? We must inform the others!
The slaves here are little more than housepets. But perhaps with some rough training, I can shape them into something useful.

My father's spirit is roaming Necris? nnDumac's curse upon him! He continues to meddle in my affairs, even in death!nnDon't believe a word he says. He's a crafty old man. No doubt death has only increased his ability to deceive.

Thank you, <<1>>. Now, go. Give the key to my son. nnI will need to test the boundaries of my new spirit form to see if I can journey to Mournhold.nnThe look on his face will last me the eternity that awaits.
<<1>> no find Stumptown?nnOver there, across water. Stumps all over. Use Mudgum Vine on saws.nn...maybe Runk give Mudgum to wrong <<1>>?
The <<1>> is saving my life!nnThe joy of release from confinement! nnThe eternity of imga gratitude!
Save yourself! There's no hope for us....
The <<1>> was good to bring me bones.
He's probably just not on his shift right now. You'll find him in the guard's barracks - his name is Gads.
Well? What'd Melves say?
Divines willing, you'll finish what I've started, <<1>>. Stay strong.

That was... not what I expected! nnSweet, yet bitter. That must be the mandrake root. I think this may be a great success!nnOf course, I'll have to taste a few more samples before I can present my findings. Excuse me.
Your arms! They are still attached!
I believe we have done all we can. Molag Bal will not have his sacrifices this day.
What have we done to deserve this? Why does the Tribunal not hear our prayers?
Bork!
My sister was always the favorite of the family. When she fell ill, it was said my own father wished it was me instead.
Have you had any luck in proving Ferema's innocence?
Jivon... he found out. My fate is sealed.nnHow unforgiving this world is. I can only pray for leniency.
Where is the tongue?  Tell me you found him and spilt his blood over the ground!
I've undone your handiwork, <<1>>. In the future, please refrain from smashing any more magical devices around my home.
Lady Elise and the other survivors of Camlorn owe you their lives.
Get a drop of the purple potion, a pinch of reagent and then combine them with the bergamont seeds in the alchemy set.
House Dres can use more allies like you, who are not afraid to apply force to what will not budge.  I have told the House Father of your work for me.
I never thought we'd live through what happened in Camlorn. Thank you.
I never thought we'd live through what happened in Camlorn. Thank you.
I never thought we'd live through what happened in Camlorn. Thank you.
I never thought we'd live through what happened in Camlorn. Thank you.
I never thought we'd live through what happened in Camlorn. Thank you.
The alit you brought are fine and healthy.nnThe ordinators of Illath Temple are grateful for your help.
test
Thank you for the snake meat. Without your help, we would have been stuck out here with no food.
Did the sujamma come out well? I hope my master was not upset at my failure...
Hurry to the northwest and kill the Scamps attacking the Lifetimber Blossom.
My sleep is back to normal now. nnFor a while, I had nightmares every night! It was horrible!
Akatosh bless you and yours, traveller!
Do you know what that armorer is charging for greaves these days? It's scandalous!
There's just not enough work around this place, even though it's a big city. nnHow am I supposed to feed my family? I blame all the outsiders.nnSo, where are you from?
The Daggerfall Covenant will finally bring peace.
There are too many new faces in Wayrest for me to keep track of everyone. nnSo have we met before?
It's no surprise that Wayrest is the capital of the Daggerfall Covenant.
The Eight be with you, traveller, no matter where you roam.
I hear we owe our recovery to your valiant efforts. nnThank you so much for restoring our minds!
Lorkhan looks after his own, anywhere heroes may roam.
Ever since I came here, my sleep's been restless. nnIt's gotten better lately, but I still feel tired most of the time.
The Bretons aren't friendly to anyone who isn't one of them.
I was expecting Wayrest to be more civilized. I am disappointed.
I am teaching history to correct errors in Breton lore. nnYou do realize, of course, that Tamrielic is really based on the Altmer language? nnMost here are surprised to learn this.
Y'ffre bless you, traveller!
Tamriel is beset with dangers on all sides these days.
I traveled beyond the Dragontail Mountains recently. nnIt is not a fitting place for the unprepared.
This one is pleased to greet you.
There aren't enough hours in the day for everything we have to do.
I practice my technique at the Fighters Guild almost every day.
Stormhaven is too cold for me. I miss the heat of the desert.
May the Divines bless you, <<1>>.

Many thanks for providing this one with food. nnStarvation would have made this one's life far more difficult. nnBesides, how can Kal-J'Rei convince others of his health when Kal-J'Rei is weakened by lack of food?
Any of the Barkbite Orcs could be carrying a trinket, but they keep the spices crated within their camp.
I feel better now.
Ahji thanks you for your help and sincerely hopes you are not torn apart by wraiths.
Wayrest is my home now. nnI don't foresee travelling beyond the Wrothgar Mountains again.
Wayrest shows how well Orcs, Redguards, and Bretons can live together in peace.
Pleased to meet you.
There aren't enough hours in the day for all the things this one must do!
I'd go back to Sentinel, but I've found a good place to live in Wayrest. nnMaybe someday, I'll go back.
It rains too much in Stormhaven for my tastes. nnOnce my work in Wayrest is done, I'm going home to Sentinel.
If you are looking to collect the bounty on Nalluth, check the woods to the west. She will be roaming about with her two accomplices. nnGood luck.
Have you discovered the results of my wife's ritual, <<1>>? nnI want to know the truth she gave her life to find.

You can enter the caves now? Excellent. nnKill <<1>>. Stop him from preying on the people of Kragenmoor.nnRemember, you don't need to kill the rabble helping him. Slaying <<1>> will be enough to stop the flow of skooma.nnEnd this.
Did you find them?
This is my first time in Wayrest. Quite the city, isn't it?
What news do you bring from the ruins? Did you solve the mystery of the Dwemer machinery?
Their voices are silent after all this time...
Head to Karthdar and collect Bottles of Jagga. The ruined town is north of Moss Lord.

As you explore the jungle, watch for any underground springs. They're scattered throughout the region, from Ebon Ro up to the Wood Orc town of Barkbite.nnBut be careful - some of them are poisoned by the waters flowing off Gil-Var-Delle.
Please tell me you've come with good news about that ship.
I made some fine soul stones out of those gems you brought me, <<1>>.  Thank you again.
Hello again my friend <<1>>.  Look at these fine viper skin boots - I tanned them with the venom you brought me.  Very effective.
Those eggs you brought were very delicious!  The miners have not stopped complaining, but at least Qa-dur's belly is full.
Mazte! The nectar of kings! nnLluthyne probably doesn't even drink anyway.
I can smell the netch scent on you. You've brought me my larvae, I hope?
From your expression, I can tell that you've seen something strange.nnHave you found the source of the tarn's corruption?
Do you have the courage to continue on this path? I could not... I was too weak.
We heard a great noise from inside the mines just now, and kwama came stampeding out in fear.  What happened?
Ihdana will never have respect for those who have enslaved her.  You, you are different. In another situation, we would be friends.
With all the bloody dead stumbling around, I'm likely to get my throat torn out!
I would have gathered more if I could. Those little creatures roaming around here just keep coming out of the blue. Another fascinating creature I'll perhaps study if I can gain access to the guild!
Manabi and I have seen and killed every manner of beast in this valley. How, then, can we not kill the ones most dangerous to our tribe?nnI ask myself this every night.
You have given me the courage to tell the Wise Woman how I feel.nnOur ancestors are wise even in their confusion, and we are foolish to think our path is righteous.
All this time, my brother and I have been searching for a way to gain entry to the Mage's Guild! nnThis may very well be the breakthrough we wanted.nnPlease, get me those results as soon as you can!
We have begun fortifying the fort again, and soon we will have established this as our new home.  Thank you for your help in securing weapons, and making sure there was warriors left to use them!
Rations at last! I was beginning to think they'd forgotten about me.
Place poultices on the sick, and the vapors will ease their pain. nnI fear I have no treatment to cure them completely, but I cannot stand by and watch people suffer.
I could use your assistance.
I'll be able to pay my crew and take on cargo now. You've saved me a trip, <<, and I'll not forget it.
What, you shaking me down for more? A deal's a deal! Half and half.
In better times, I'd melt these poor excuses for weapons down for cutlery.nnWe have no time to nitpick craftmanship, as much as it pains me. The others best know how to use a sword!
It's a shame we had to lose two ordinators over this mess.nnAt the very least, Vusara proved to be a traitor.nnHe would have been executed regardless.

After the battle of Stonefalls, the Mages Guild sent several groups of us out to search the area. You might have come across several of us already, but we're all about. Never know what type of Arkavari technology we might come across.

The Mages Guild study more than just the art of working with magicka. Relic hunters and historians like ourselves are often sent out on various missions to research any magical entities that are out in the lands of Tamriel.
Have you any news of the war?
Would you please retrieve brains from the creatures of Cormount and return them to me?
What are we going to do? How will be get our town back?
Just a few more errands, and then I can get out of this infernal place.
Lovely darling, you have saved my village from the savages! You give us hope that things may yet return to the way they once were. Bless you my dear! May the gods guard your steps.

I've dedicated my sanatorium to easing the pain of the plague's victims.nnHowever, my patience and resources only go so far.nnI can't maintain a semblance of order whenever a madman meanders over and mauls me.
My love! I know he must be here somewhere, but I'm so afraid.nnOh, my cursed heart!nnHe must be on top of one of the other towers. He must be!
Have you come from the east? Have you heard any news of my village, Brukbrook?
A drink for our good friend... what was your name again?  Oh, yes, our good friend <<1>>.  <<1>> with the rum, our very good friend.
We have seen many of the people you sent in Quarantine.  Thank you for your help in trying to contain the Blight here.
I hope you're having luck with those ash reeds. nnI used to be able to gather them with ease, but an influx of mudcrabs has made that quite difficult for me.
Freedom from the beasts, at last a-long! We are in your debt, <<1>>.
Those lying charlatans are everywhere around this city.nnGo! Exact my vengeance!
This one has enjoyed your company, Ventures-Much.
You should leave, <<1>>. Slip out through the vines while you can. There's no hope for us.
A job well done, my friend. nnPlease let <<1>> know at your earliest convenience. nnShe's usually by the front of the temple entrance.
The stench of Daedric corruption is dissipating.
The rank stench of death lingers upon you. You've collected the mort flesh for me, haven't you?
I feel so lost. If the Three truly exist, why do they leave me in such darkness?

Please, speak to my sister Kireth if you have not already. Eagerly she awaits ways to test her newest creation - small creatures made from bits and pieces of Dwemer parts. I know it sounds maddening, but that girl truly has a way with her creations.

These little critters here are made with the finest bolts and scraps picked up through my various travels. Amazing what you can do with winding some gears together and letting them go!nnIf anything this trip may give me time to test them out!
Good to see you again, my friend. I'm feeling much happier already, thanks to you.

The Ebonheart Pact would release all the slaves, but it only seem to exist for lizards and northmen.nnHouse Dres doesn't seems to care a whit about the Pact.nnI just want to get out of these blasted lands. Maybe I'll see Orsinium again before I die.

I brought my wife and son to the keep.nnI had to see if House Dres had a treatment for this plague spreading through Stonefalls. They couldn't offer us more than words.nnIf we must travel to a Tribunal temple, then that's what we will do.
You are looking for the Antler Crown. It is in the throne room. Take it from Phrastus.
Our caravan has stopped for a brief respite. I pray that the wagons hold until we get to Deshaan.
I was hoping to travel to Kragenmoor, but the roads are too dangerous. Even the wildlife is mad with this disease.
I was hoping to travel to Kragenmoor, but the roads are too dangerous. Even the wildlife is mad with blight.
You still stand before me, stranger? Do you intend to try and stop our party from completing our duty and forsake the Tribunal?
Your smell makes my stomach rumble and my jaws salivate.nnTalk quickly, meat.
There are days the Three test our ability to endure.nnThis is surely one of mine.
Thank you so much again for finding my things inside the tombs.nnIt won't be long before I'm ready to give contacting my ancestor another try.nnI'm sure I'll have better luck this time!
The urn must be destroyed so that they may be free! It's not too late... it can't be!
The urn must be destroyed so that they may be free! It's not too late... it can't be!
Thank you for returning our family's treasures, <<1>>.

I am well trained in countering necromantic spells.nnOnce I can make the proper preparations, I'll see these spirits rest in peace again.nnThe gates of Necris open to those who wish to pay their respects.

My thanks for your help, friend. I apologize for imposing upon you, but I am glad you were able to assist and keep our little party going. Please, make yourself at home and avail yourself of my estate. My home is your home.
We can clean up the rest from here. Quick, get to Commander Viskel! He needs reinforcements!
Be careful you're not seen.
Did you really kill all those Imperials? Dear gods...
You know, I could get used to working with someone like you.
Heard you got those stingy horsemen to part with a few steeds. Can't thank you enough!
Smiling at the <<1>>.nnIs the <<1>> tasting the fine Amberberry wine?
The spring's south of the village. Use the poison while you stand in it.
Will the <<1>> be speaking to Shoom outside the cave?
Waiting for Yoon to return.nnWill the <<1>> be saving Yoon from Shoof's kicks and punches?nnPraising the <<1>> for courage and bravery....
Maybe the <<1>> will be saving Yoon from Shoof's kicks and bites when Yoon returns?
Tokutu, Sentry <<1>>!
I can talk about my son all day long if you like. I do love him so. I just hope he eventually straightens himself out.
The fitful return of breath. The fluttering beat of a frightened heart quieting.
Did you find any survivors?
Seeing the <<1>> carry Baf's satchel! nnThe elation of relief! nnAvoiding tragedy and loss!

Another <<1>>! They will not allow me to pass anywhere near the ruins below us.nnI regret making this shocking pronouncement, but in the name of knowledge, they must be destroyed!nnAnd you, my friend, shall be the agency of their elimination!
Lady Sofia is a hero in the eyes of history, but she was cursed in her lifetime. She rebelled against her lord, Merovec, in a valiant attempt to save the queen.
More than what I have said, I do not know. If the curse can be reversed, so relieved I would be.
I'm absolutely fine, now that I've got my shovel back. nnYou go on and do your heroic deeds. I'll just hide here until the bloodfiends run out of victims to eat and wander off.

I commune with the spirits here. nnWhen the spirits of this place learned I could hear them, they flooded my mind with their voices, thoughts, and memories.nnIt is as though they are crushing my consciousness....
Use the stone I gave you to calm aggressive spriggans.
We've won the day. Well fought, friend.nnI've ordered my soldiers to reinforce the redoubt. They've found new resolve from our victory here today.
I'll rest here for a moment before I return home. If you slay that wicked creature, please come see me in Crosswych,
Outlanders bring trouble with them. Look at what happened to the Spriggans.
Your hands are too clean. You're not from around here.
A scamp has the Peatwalker totem. nnI saw it run into the ruins north of here. Could you bring it back to me, hero?
You wouldn't last a minute against Old Snaptooth. nnJust so you know.

My life isn't easy. I'm always on the road with mercenaries. We take what comforts we can.nnA missing kitten may seem like a small matter to you, but I'll never have a wife or family.nnLeia is my one bright light in a dark and bloody world. Thanks.

Kindly walk over to the Peatwalker village to the west, claim one of their sages, and escort him back here.nnBe careful not to be spotted by a Peatwalker. They won't hesitate to attack a stranger to Lushwallow.
She feels her life ebbing now. nnAll her power is gone, but you have done her a great service.  nnNow go. She would not have you see her ending.
I ate them all. Get away from me! Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I killed them all. Why would I remember that? Why? nnGet away from me!
I killed them all. Why would I remember that? Why? nnGet away from me!
I killed them all. Why would I remember that? Why?nnGet away from me!
I killed them all. Why would I remember that? Why? nnGet away from me!
I killed them all. Why would I remember that? Why?nnGet away from me!
They'll be singing your name all the way back in Wayrest!
They'll be singing your name all the way back in Wayrest!
They'll be singing your name all the way back in Wayrest!
They'll be singing your name all the way back in Wayrest!
Thank you! With your help, we'll be able to stay here much longer. We can endure anything the elements bring to us.nnAs soon as he calms down, I'm going to take all our ale and dump it in the bog.
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
I ate them all. Get away from me. Why would I have to remember that? Why?
Thank you. I don't know how you found me, but I'm glad you did.
Thanks for finding my pickaxe, friend.
It's good to see the foals returning.
I'm glad you were able to escape the cave unharmed.
You saved me a lot of trouble. The dockmaster would have had a nice little chat with me if I lost all that ale.nnGood thing I didn't drink it all... I mean, I didn't let the mudcrabs take it all.
Thanks for your help, <<1>>.nnNow that my bow is fixed, I think I might stay here a bit longer and hunt some more. nnNext time, I'll harvest my own sinew, just in case my bow snaps again.
Our true foe is fear in the face of adversity.
I could hear Piers calling for help from here
target: he can't be that far away.

source: Raoul always liked to live dangerously. He's probably made it to the deepest parts of the mine: the Western or Eastern Ends.
Piers began fending off an attack from the undead not long after we entered the mine.nnI believe he's still in the mine's Upper Tunnel.
They say these risen miners were once our friends. Someone with unspeakable power brought them back to life.nnI've never seen anything like this before....
Elder Brump will be climbing a tree and racing back to Cliffvoot.nnWill <<1>> tell Yoon of Elder Brump's release?
Thank you for your assistance. It's best you don't tarry. My killers may storm the room at any moment, and our prophecies are equally grim.nnI'd say "good luck," but... well, you know.
I'll rest here a bit longer. When I feel a little better, I'll head back to town.
How can I help you, friend? Are you in need of any supplies?
Have you found my betrothed yet?
Did you find the ring?  Thank you for doing this.  I'm sorry about Gustave, I really am.
Serge is long dead, but his creation remains.
<<1>>'s house is just outside Crosswych to the south. His house might be surrounded by the same spectres that lurked outside Mari's home.
Please take care of this Daedra business. I've invested too much, run this estate too well to watch it go to pieces from a field!
<The spirit stares at you in silence.>
I do apologize for sending you on such a wild goose chase. A mother can't help but worry for her kin.nnWon't you take a moment to speak with her?
You are a spiteful person, you know that? After I begged you not to tell... you try and ruin me anyways!
You look like the sort who can appreciate our finest dessert specialties.
Friend, you have eased my pain. I don't know how much longer I'll still draw breath, but I'll bless your name with my last.
If any type of ritual is going to take place, it's going to be in that house. nnWho knows? Maybe you'll get lucky. Maybe you'll only find a rocky mountainside.nnI doubt it, though.
It is an honor to know you, <<1>>.  Your spirit and bravery can only be equaled by your ferocity in battle.
Denthis once wanted a spell to make people taller and heavier. He said it would give us "parity" in dealing with the Nords. nnHe's an idiot. A thieving idiot.
Let me know how it ends.

Every day that Aurelia woman sends her servants over to demand wine. Every day I laugh in their faces.nnI'd say Y'ffre help her husband, but if she's stuck here and he isn't, the Green Lord's already seen to it. The woman's a hoarvor.
Once you've gotten rid of that cat, I feel confident that things will turn around.
My family herded highland cows for generations. nnThe Watchers protect all who revere the mammoths. They're probably the distant kin of our precious cows!
I've heard legends of the spirits speaking to the penitent. nnPerhaps it's too much to hope for, but I must keep to my faith.
Things are settling down. Soon, we'll best these filthy ogres.

As soon as I saw you, I had a good feeling. nnWe can do this. We just have to watch out for the slavers' leader, Ma'jhad Kha. Avoid him at all costs. The fires should keep him busy though.nnIf you got questions, ask. Otherwise, good luck.
Did you find him? Did he like his gift? You did tell him it was from me, didn't you?
Ah, the poor, delusional girl. I almost feel bad for her.nnIf you wish, you may visit her in the guard barracks where she is being held.

Freeing these spirits won't be as simple as slashing down a beast and going on your way.nnEach spirit still lingers for its own reasons. Show them the light. Guide their way.nnGuess wrong, however, you'll put your life in danger.
You have done well.
Have you found her? nnMy sight... it's fading....
Our deal is over, dear <<1>>. nnKnow that I'll remember you fondly.
Whatever Murk-Watcher has asked you to do, this one hopes you keep her best interest in mind.
I feel like a new man already, friend. Sooner we hit the road the better, far as I'm concerned. nnDro-Dara says he's just about ready. Now we just need to round up Murk-Watcher. I hope she'll come.
I am prepared to complete the incantation. Then we will get vengeance against the bandits. Will you join me?

Oh, it's lovely to give your love a single perfect rose / It's lovelier still to do the same not wearing any clothes. / Oh, it's lovely to abandon all your cares and fears and woes / It's lovelier still to do the same not wearing any clothes.
Tough luck, friend. Jazha was a killer, and no mistake. nnI guess today, wisdom beat youth!nnCare to place a bet on the next fight?
This Blackmaul mercenary is dead.
Don't mind me. I just need a bit of rest before I head back. You go on without me.
Don't give away my position. This is a good vantage point for observing the ogres.
Valenwood is more dangerous than stories describe - not everyone escapes the forest to tell a tale.
Thank you for your help. This is going to be perfect now. Perfect. nnI don't know whether I'm happy or sad, or both, but I feel better.
There is no glory in killing innocents - General Cruor slaughtered the unarmed citizens of this town.nnHe must pay!
Ithguleoir is dead? I can hardly believe it! nnHenri can finally start fishing again. He certainly can't use Ithguleoir as an excuse anymore!
What did you find in the village? I'm breathless with anticipation.
Someone tell General Godrun to hurry up and give us our orders! If there's to be another battle, let's get on with it!
The western road goes to the farms. <<1>> has a sister who ran that way.nnTell <<2>> she must pray. Never stop praying!
Why'd you come all the way back down here?nn<<1>> was one of those conscripts. If he survived, he'll be closer to that cave than this.
We are done talking. Leave us to our suffering.
Do be careful near the rocks to the north! nnI will wait for your return, dear <<1>>.nnOh, I'm blushing! How silly of me.

What I wouldn't give for a company of trained Orcs! Godrun keeps sending us these Bosmer and Argonians.nnI sent word to my family to join us. Even my youngest is a better soldier than these conscripts.
I don't know how long the blood you gathered will slake Marcel's thirst.nnI hope it's long enough for us to make our way to <<1>>.
Something is wrong. These ruins are centuries old, yet power still stirs here.nnIt's pulling at my very soul.
Thank you again for your help with the fish and nereids. We need all the help we can get.
Have you saved my sister yet?
Most of the interesting markers and stones are up in the ruins. nnThere aren't as many down here. Not as many hauntings, either.
It is brave of you to dare the waters where Weerhat's boat was attacked. nnDid you find anything?
I must figure out how to breach this wall. I am sorry, <<1>> - I do not yet have a course of action.
As soon as I gather my strength I'll go to Oldgate and let them know about Lieutenant Gagnon. Thank you again for your help.
We put our lives into your hands. Bring that cavern down on their heads!
Great job, <<1>>!nn<<2>> wouldn't have survived without your help.
Now that was a fight to remember! Hah! I'm sure the Blackmauls will remember it for a while.nnMaybe they'll keep their distance now.
I have no time to talk! I must collect the bodies!
You spoke with King Faume! Doesn't he have a toad for an eye or something? I never understood that -- was his eye a toad or an eye?
King Faume will curse me for having you smash Daedric idols in his barrow. It had to happen, though! nnYou just gave us a clear advantage over these monsters.
Watching the ruins. nnNot seeing the friendly, happy villagers. nnNot giving up.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! You have succeeded then?
I was hoping they would burn this place down. Breton buildings are an eye sore.
Did you really kill all those Imperials? Dear gods...
Dead bears, dead men. Creatures of the Valenwood will eat well tonight!
This disease is spreading. nnI'm not sure how many more resources we'll need to to sacrifice for the war in <<1>>.
It's a good thing you came along. Your help is certainly appreciated.
You bring word from the Imperial Palisade?
Please find Vaden for me. nnLet him know I realize what I've done, and I'm sorry. nnI just want to see him again in my final moments.
Please leave me alone. I have nothing to say to you.
I am a humble acolyte within the temple. Otherwise, I would have prayer books of my own. nnOnly curates and diviners are allowed to handle the sermons of the Almsivi.

You have truly helped me. Others would have offered naught but empty consolation, but you have helped me.nnWhen I think of all the lives lost, I find no solace.nnI have no other wish than to die here quietly, far from the horrors I have seen.
<You've found a body. It's warm, but lifeless.>
I have no doubt. The fiends simply killed her when they found her. nnThey're probably desecrating her body right now, even as we speak.
Behind the temple is a great waterfall. nnGo beneath it. Find the hidden entry into the temple.
What is that contraption you hold? The head of a Kwama?nnPlease... get it away from me. I cannot abide such things.
You must act quickly, <<1>>! nnIf the Vereansu suspect we are moving against them, they will surely retaliate.
We were very fortunate to have you pass through here. nnYou uncovered and removed a great threat to House Hlaalu.nnFor that, we thank you.

If the council found out I was commandeering resources instead of providing them to the troops, they'd exile me... or worse.nnThey also expect me to prevent their city from falling to the Ashlanders.nnYou know what? One or the other. I can't do both.
If something has happened to her, I shall never forgive myself.
Leave me to my sorrow, accursed stranger. I never want to see your face again.
If someone within our enterprise has been selling weapons to the Vereansu, I must know. This must stop.nnThe people of Narsis shouldn't find out that we've been working against ourselves.
You're a credit to your race, soldier. nnIf you can collapse that cavern, Clan Murtag will be in your debt, and we pay our debts.
Please! Free me! It's too much for me to bear.
I'm sure Galus heard the impact of the rockslide. He must be deeply concerned over what has taken place here. Please bring word to him as soon as possible.
I need to get back to my family. Please get me out of here!

I wish I could pay the ransom, but gathering that much money would make my wife suspicious.nnIf she found out about you-know-who, she'd... well, I don't want to think about that.nnIt's best she doesn't find out.
I don't know who you are, but I suppose I should thank you.nnSo... thank you for bringing this matter to my attention. nnI'll make sure she doesn't bother us again.
You have returned, my friend! nnWhat can House Hlaalu do for you?
A town of iniquity, vice, and a terrible smell, to top it off! I plan to book the soonest caravan to Mournhold to return to my previous posting.
Thanks for taking care of those zombies!  Now I can head back back to town.  I'll let Captain Yarborough know you helped out here.
How did you learn about my father's sword, <<1>>?
Enjoying the failure of Wud. nnSavoring your victory.nnAdmiring the stranger's achievement!
Wud amuses himself at Hoom's expense. nnThe hilarity of the drained coconuts! The gratifying wet sound heard as it coats the rival.
Be not afraid. You need fear nothing from my brothers and sisters of the blade.

Welcome to Shinji's Scarp. Once a quaint villagenow a warzone.nnGrandmaster Durak told us to be on the lookout for you. He's expecting you, so come on into the camp. nnKeep your weapon handy though. Don't forget there's a battle going on.
Three other towers once stood in Aphren's Hold. nnTake my sword to each one. Then I can finally join my sister's fight.
Where did you come from?
Don't worry about us. We'll be fine.nnI've got enough traps set up around here. nnIf any scamp dares to get close enough, he'll trigger one... and end up in a ball of flame.
These are sacred grounds. My sacred grounds. They are not meant for the living. nnAre you the one who disturbs our rest?
You must free the sick captives. They may be ill, but they don't deserve to suffer at the hands of the Vereansu.
A lot of people owe you their lives for what you did here.
I'm sorry about those scamps getting through. It was pretty frantic down here!

Ugly brute! Your stench is overwhelming! I cannot imagine how a pig child could attempt to pass as one of Alessia's faithful.nnNow tell me what business you have here, deep within the last refuge of the Maruhkites?
I'm finishing up here and then heading back to the hideout. nnIf you're up for a little adventure, though, I might have something else for you.
You have done well.
You have done well.
I have seen my sister's last days. nnI have fought beside her. nnThank you.
I know what I must do to win her heart. It's dangerous, but I think it will work.
While you are under the spell's influence, you'll walk the line between dreams and reality.nnI'll watch over your body after you've fallen asleep.
We have little time to strike. We must succeed, or all is lost.
I must pack a few things for my trip to Narsis.nnThen I'll say goodbye and make sure my family is taken care of.nnThank you, friend.
It's a good thing you came along. Your help is appreciated.
You truly are a divine gift from Azura. Right when I asked for it, too. I'll never doubt the power of prayer again.
That fool didn't learn his lesson. nnHe keeps babbling on and on. He wants to send another team back into the mines to dig.nnY'know, you'd think we'd have lost enough lives already.
Even now, goblins pour barrels of poison in the stream by Westtry. That river runs all the way to Aldcroft. Soon, their people will sicken like ours... unless you can stop the goblins.
The area around us holds many places to hide. nnI'm sure he's slipped into one. nnHe must have.

Be careful getting that robe! There's a lot of acolytes in the mine.nnI'm glad to have you as a companion... just not enough to help you after you run back here with all of them chasing you.nnUh, I'll just tidy up a bit. Good luck finding things out!
I can feel that stranger looking at me. nnI bet he's not a real mender.nnI wonder what he really is?
You're back. Did you fulfill my orders, acolyte? nnDid you follow them... exactly? I grow tired of asking this.
We're so close! So... close....nnAfter all this time, our work will finally pay off. nnThe Master will rise once more! Then we will....nnWait. Who are you? I don't recognize your face.

I'll make sure all access to the chambers is cut off. None shall pass! nnI'll join you, just you as soon as I can. I'll be back here! Guarding!nnI'll also see if I can muster up more courage. This "being a coward" thing really takes a lot of work.

Sorick admitted it, and he's paying  reparations? He should be paying with his life! At least he's leaving. You know how nobles are. They'll never convict him.nnYou've saved us and our homes. We are grateful.
Have you talked to that useless husband of mine yet?
Did you get the ring from Miranda?
Baron Sorick's men were here. They killed my husband!nnPlease, I  I won't say a word about the eggs. I swear! I won't tell anyone!
If only we hadn't finished the wine so quickly! nnI fear to stand up, lest I fall into the mud again.
The irrigation system works from the central well. nnI'll clean it out while you get down to the paddies. Then you can wash out the contaminated water.
I need more caps for my fishing poison.nnWhat? You never heard of fishing with poison?nnYou don't look like a fisherman. How would you know?
Shaleen can't hide forever. nnHe'll be back.

He's not a talkative one, is he? nnAh, well! Doubtless I will have to school him on the teachings of philosophers. Our heated debates will have to come in time! nnHow fortuitious. I seem to have plenty of time on my hands.

I doubt they'd understand you well enough.nnThey can't simply offer up the deed if you ask for it like a civilized person. nnIt's best to put them out of their misery first. Then you should have no problem taking the deeds from them.
This existence cannot last much longer. nnNow that Ervyna is dead, I've resolved the last regret that allowed me to cling to life.nnThank you, <<1>>.
Surely, you now see why this was necessary. nnThis vile operation must end.

Hmm. The herbs are a bit strong. Instead of mellowing the cheap wine's flavor, it just makes it more acidic.nnIf you add some dirt, it'll add depth and complexity. The dried flowers should provide a nice floral note.
Don't forget to get your work orders signed. nnI know how much everyone enjoys paperwork. If you remember, we'll have less of it.
Your timely arrival in Aldsotha was more than a mere coincidence. nnYou helped defend our town, and we'll think of you as a hero for years to come.
Poor Endal. He was one of my closest friends. He didn't deserve this....
You can imagine my shock when I heard the news.nnI never would have guessed that <<1>> wasn't really a noble of House Indoril.nnI'm certainly glad you exposed her.
They burned my stall. They burned my wares! nnI'll have to start all over. I can only salvage a few workable scraps from what's left.

I fear the Daedric portal you closed allowed more of them through than I anticipated.nnThe Dremora Lord brought many under its control. nnImagine the numbers we might be facing if you hadn't acted when you did.
I sense you found a way to contact the elder. nnIs this true?
Ah, you have come, it is well! But where is Lyris? Has she abandoned the cause at last? No, no. That cannot be, it is not written so.nnGo find our Titanborn. Bring her here.
The sounds of battle outside have subsided. nnI can only assume your efforts here are responsible.
I heard you're helping <<1>> deal with the grave-robbing in the Bonebarrows.nnDon't forget that <<2>> needs help as well.
Untouched! It's amazing. All of my wares are completely intact. nnI can't help but think it was because I stayed behind. nnPoor Hrenil fled, and they set fire to his stall!
In my heart, I knew the Imperials wouldn't negotiate. I had to try. I had a responsibility to try.
I have a lot to think about, <<1>>. nnPlease, leave me to my thoughts.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! You have succeeded then?
Sorick should be in the pool directly behind us.nnJust enter the pool and drop the egg in the water.
Please find Vaden for me. Let him know I realize what I have done, and I am sorry. I just want to see him again in my final moments.
I'd go with you, but I can't disobey Master Altien.nnPlease take the scroll to him.
The arena is just beyond here. nnSpeak to the weaponmaster. She'll call forth our champion. nnDon't worry about hurting her. Fight to survive. She won't hold back.
I can see that many of the smaller fires have been extinguished. Thank you for volunteering to help us.
It's only right that you should be the one to return the Dream Shard to its place with Azura.nnWe would be honored if you would place the shard upon the statue.
Good luck out there! I'm sure you'll be fine. nnSearch everything. I wouldn't want you to miss anything.
I knew you'd do it. Abbot Durak is awake!
The Loqueach River is the only terrain I can think of that might be affecting this area. nnI've noticed that the wildlife near the Korgathi River seems to be much healthier.
Thank you. nnThank you for saving me.
Something as pristine as Altmertown could never survive in Grahtwood. Thanks again for helping to wash the clean away.

We use most of this ore to make weapons and armor for our clients. That's not to say we don't keep a share for ourselves....nnYou might have noticed: the more ore we gather, the more supplies we have avaliable... just in case anything bad happens....
He's waiting for us by the upstairs hearth. Let's not keep him.
Ahh! The smell of fresh goblin blood is like perfume to me. nnI knew I could count on you.
Help me regain my power, and we will help you against Angof.
Thanks for talking to Gerarde. He's the sort that doesn't take 'no' for an answer.nnI was afraid he'd convince me to do something dangerous if I went to the Moonlit Maw myself!
Help us regain our power, and we will help you against Angof.
Most of our guild is at the beach house outside Wayrest. I'm going to join them. nnI want spend the rest of my days lazing about on the beach.
We owe you a debt of gratitude, <<1>>! nnWe'll never forget your kindness.
Meet me outside this cave. I must ready for my escape.
You've got to help me. Those goblins will eat me!
That totem's got to come down from the tower, or we'll never be rid of these Goblins.nnBlast you, Rama! I'll have your hide for this.
It is good to count you among our number. If you need anything of the Guild, don't hesitate to ask.
The stench of the jungle is less pervasive since you cleared Altmertown of the diseased weeds.
Thank you, <<1>>.nn You've allowed both of us to be together again.
Once the bodies have been burned, we'll finally be free of this mortal realm.

No one listens to me! nnI've worked with plants all my life, but because I'm a simple Oathman, my ideas are useless to them. They won't even hear me out. nnInstead. I'm stuck tending to these dumb creatures all day.
I'd recommend you avoid taking a swim in the tar while you're out there.nnGet us the samples first. Then we'll figure out how to get those guar back.
You're quick, <<1>>, as I knew you would be.nnA runecrafter must be intelligent and lucky. Clearly, you're already blessed by the Eight with those traits.
Best of luck to you. Those bottles are sealed rather well, so hopefully, no damage has come to them.
Those gloves should come in especially handy, if you can find them.
Let me guess: one of the guards tried to extort money from you, right?nnNo matter how many times you tell those idiots we don't do this for money....
What, you again? Don't you have some work to do?
How fares the task? Do you have it yet?nnPerhaps you need to take a more forceful approach. My patience is wearing thin.
Were you successful? I hope you bring good news. The stress is almost too much to bear.
The Supernal Dreamers are all over the shoreline. It might be wise to find something that could help mask your presence.

The guards aren't interested in anything I've offered, but I have an idea that might work. nn<<1>>'s brother, Rahar, was recently murdered. Perhaps you can turn them against one another by suggesting <<2>> is under investigation for it.

If you want to help, I won't stop younnEvery scholar and explorer has a different idea about how to handle the flower. No one ever wants to try his own method, though. You can consult with everyone, if you like. nnI can't say how useful that will be.
It was foolish of them to attack us. I believe they sought to catch us off-guard, and were surprised when we had anticipated their betrayal.
I've used the same poultice on myself that you used on the other wardens. I should be fine. nnSeriously, don't worry. Go on now.
You got 5 coppers? I just ne- hic! Just need to rent a boar to get home.nnI'm fine. I can ride.
The Feladrim will fall....
You've heard my people's stories and their reason for fighting.nnI hope you understand the importance of what stand for now.nnIn fact, we'd be honored to have you join us, if you're still interested.

Ah! Always good to see a new face around here! nnPlease, have a seat. Share a meal with us. I've been working on it all day. nnBoiled cliff racer meat! It used to be my husband's favorite dish.nnCome now. Don't be shy.
This area is off limits. Leave now before I slit your throat!
Count Hosni doesn't like guests entering his treasury. You should leave before you find yourself with my sword in your gut.
I asked Abbot Durak to go downstairs because I wanted to speak with you for a few moments alone.nnTell me something. Do you recall everything that happened in the dream?
I don't know what else you want from me. Leave me alone!
Walk softly, please. I had one too many last night at the Cloudy Dregs.nnYou tromping across the deck sounds like someone hammering a two-handed mace against the side of my head.
Hilani is relieved and thankful that you've found Thomin.nnThis one may finally return to Wayrest. S'rashi is probably growing impatient with Hilani.
You look as if you've had some run-ins with the alit around here.
I have nothing to say to you.
This doesn't look too bad....
You've shown true bravery today.
The hoarvor mostly come at night. Mostly.
I wasn't always like this. I had dreams as a girl.
Regardless of whether Teshmul is a spy or a thief, I'm determined to make an example of him. nnI'd like to see how he'd fare in a pit of rabid alits.
I bet my last coins on Jazha.
Isn't this exciting?
This makes me want wrestle a slouchbear.nnYou think I could beat a slouchbear?
This doesn't make me a bad person, does it?
Isn't this exciting?
I bet my last coins on Shanari.
Poor Endal. He was one of my closest friends.nnHe didn't deserve this.

They took Christophe, one of our spirit wardens. They said his soul was the perfect match.nnDo you know what that means? I think they're going to fuse his soul with the Book of Circles. They'll sacrifice him to create their ultimate weapon!
You did well. My companions were able to enter the cave and look for our people, thanks to you.

They took Christophe, one of our spirit wardens. They said his soul was the perfect match.nnDo you know what that means? I think they're going to fuse his soul with the Book of Circles. nnThey'll sacrifice him to create their ultimate weapon!
Please, <<1>>, if you have the key to this cage, unlock it.
Thank you for freeing our captured friends.
I watched you fight in the ring!nnI was rooting for you the whole time! nnIt's really an honor to meet you.
I saw you fight <<1>>. You were amazing!
Lots of hungry spectators are sitting on the ruins around the center ring. nnHurry! Hurry!
Better and better! It's been weeks since I faced an opponent as worthy as you!
The Mages Guild will expel me if they learned of what I did....
Seeing the Vereansu get cut down was very satisfying. nnThat should assuage my pain for a while.
I didn't care much for House Hlaalu when I first arrived.nnAfter what I've been through, I can't thank the Three enough for their help.
With the shock of that rock slide, I don't think the Vereansu even knew what hit them.
The focusing crystals are in place and we have the oil. nnGo ahead and relight the signal fire. The honor's all yours.
I think I've got a message with your name on it. Are you <<1>>?nnI guess you'd rather meet a messenger than a hired killer, right?nnWatch your step.
I find life as an apprentice in Wayrest much more interesting than being a farmer over in Gavaudon.

Go do your thing, friend. Watch out for Ma'jhad Kha though. nnCaptain Angarthal was just one of his lieutenants. A brute, really. This Ma'jhad Kha is a spectre from seafarer ghost storiesa dark legend that I didn't even believe until now.
I'm sure Galus heard the impact of that rockslide. nnHe must be deeply concerned about what happened here. nnPlease tell him as soon as possible.
Have you spoken to the guard captain yet? nnHe should be near the western entrance.
Have you been to Hammerfell? I hear it's made entirely of sand! They rebuild it after every windstorm. That's what they say, anyway.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! How did that ring work out for you? Have you used it yet? You really should, you know....
I was in such a hurry. I left my stall wide open. nnThat entrepreneur is a fool! Bildrin should have fled when he had the chance.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?
This existence cannot last much longer. nnNow that Ervyna is dead, I've resolved the last regret binding me to this world.nnThank you, <<1>>.
Please. You must get us out of here. There's a key somewhere. nnLook for the first mateshe may be somewhere outside the slavers' camp.nnPlease help us.
I'm embarrassed at how I behaved.nnI put my own position in the court above the safety of Alcaire's people. nnNever again.
You have helped me more than you could know, but I ask that you leave me in my last moments. I wish to rest here for a bit longer.
I'm keeping an eye out for the Daedra, <<1>>. They won't fool me again so easily.nnBlessed Arkay gave me a loving wife, the best children, and good friends... friends like you.
Looks like you've given me a reason to improve my skills... even further.

Now we just need to do something about Duchess Lakana. She's still intent on sending our loyal Breton guards and soldiers back home.nnIf we don't do something about her, I swear, someone else will....
Did you poison the slavers' wine?
What possessed those servants of the Tribunal? How could they spirit away our sick and dying? nnWe shouldn't have trusted the priests of the temple. That was a mistake.
Why would the priests bury me, only to have their servants exhume me?nnYou must find out their purpose. Whatever it is, you must stop them.
We must make haste to the Diviner. nnWho knows what evil this artifact may bring if it lingers here any longer!
I can't believe you saved them all!
I must be vigilant. I must watch for these madmen, even while I'm figuring out how to save them.nnPlease, don't bother me again until you've found the source of this madness.
Dig deep to the root of the school. nnPlace the remedy where it will do the most good.
Well, well. So you're back, eh? nnI can't wait to hear what you've got to say. Really.
Keep moving, stranger. There's nothing down here for anyone on our side of the issue.
Accusing one of the Great Houses of high treason is a brazen act indeed!nnWhat shall come of this, I wonder?
Your path lies to the northeast. It wanders through the ruined gates of Nychthemeral. nnYou must destroy Patriarch Leyden before he causes more harm to our people.
Who's there? I can't seem to... I can't open my eyes anymore.
Bosmer and Imperials working together. What's the world coming to?
You defeated my bear! What delightful carnage!
I see you didn't get your head chewed off, like the last two. nnStill got both arms, as well.
Hang the scamp scarecrow on a post in the field. nnHurry! Before they find us! I don't want to end up like Farmer Vanne.
These cultists have likely spread their wickedness to other places in Stormhaven.nnSomeone should do something  before it's too late!
You know what you have to do. nnDestroy the siphons. Kellisa must die.
Your task lies ahead of you. nnCleanse the roots of the parasites. Then purify the Master Wizard.
I am eternally grateful for your help, friend! nnWithout your brave assistance, I doubt I could have wrested my amulet back from the clutches of those crazed zealots.
When Sir Hughes comes back, I hope we'll be able to eliminate the bandits altogether. nnGetting our tabards back was a good start though.

The writ will be yours, but not until you deal with some writs of our own. nnThey're not officially sanctioned. That's why I need someone like you to aid us.nnBlood will be spilled, but this time, it won't be yours.
Hurry up! Untie me! Help me escape!
So many tribes gone from High Rockthe Ratfarmers, the Throatcutters, even the famous Disembowelers. The Stonechewers are really the last of the breed.
S'Rashi wishes you a long and profitable life.
You know what the problem is, right? nnThen why are you still here?
The creatures! They've stopped scratching at the walls.
You're going to save us? I pray for your safety.
I hope the area won't be too hard to find. I will be leaving here shortly, so I won't arouse too much suspicion. I may be able to catch up with you there.
While watching Teshmul, you'll have the run of the place. None of my mercenaries should get in your way.
Thank you for your help. I need you to free the others.
If you haven't got the coin, we can always look into... alternatives.
I can't say we've got the best ale around, but we sure beat the prices in Mournhold!
Hurry up! Please! Do whatever you have to do! Just get me out of here!
If I have to clean up vomit one more time today, I'm adding more water to the kegs.
If you need some rest, you've come to the right place. nnHere we strive to make your stay more enjoyable... any way we can.
I've got my eye on you, stranger.
There's gotta be something else I can use as collateral.
Now this is a real sport!
No reason to go hungry around here. What can I get you?
A Breton murdered the Duchess. nnMark my words. They're butchers!
Kill Mother Helene, and meet me at the bottom of the mountain.
All that racket down at the ship is making my head ache. I wish that ship would set sail already.
I have been waiting here for days. nnLord Saren should have sent a messenger with better connections.
Used to be a salvager, till I hired on the Midnight Swell.
Used to be a salvager, till I hired on the Midnight Swell.
I don't know why a <<1>> is interested in Dwemer lore, but it's nice to have him play after dinner.
Find our <<1>>. Escort her up to our base camp. nnThey'll need her expertise to keep the Dwemer machines from escaping the ruins.nnGo now! Her life is in danger. I... I'd never forgive....nnJust go!
Used to be a salvager, till I hired on the Midnight Swell.
Used to be a salvager, till I hired on the Midnight Swell.
Have you destroyed any eggs yet? You'll find them throughout the mine. Just smash them when you find them.
I think we'll be heading back to Alcaire Castle soon. nnI'm done with this wretched place.

You've honored my last request and helped set my fears to rest. I die knowing my duty has been done.nnPlease report the situation in the village to a constable at the camp south east of the village. Farewell.
Please let Valentin know I'm sorry I accused him of sabotage. He's on the west dock.
I must resume my investigation straight away! nnAs soon as I have a bite to eat....
That's enough of you running in and out, stirring up the villagers.nnWe can't have any more of that. Off with you, now!
You have no idea how relieved I am. I finally have Gulpi back, alive and well. nnThose alits would have torn him apart!
Yes! I heard the thunder of my children. The king cannot deny me much longer.
I just need you to set fire to any corpses you come across, okay? Keep your head down though. I don't imagine the trolls will much like what you're doing to their dinner.
Whatever she did to me  it really hurt. I thought she would kill us both! I don't know how you did that, but thank you.nnDo you have the Water Stone?
What's going on? Have you news of Lord Saren? nnThe last time I saw him, he was taking you down into the ruin.

How sad. I won't get a chance to examine the centurions myself. Master Sadryon won't let anyone down into the ruins.nnSuch a pity! Imagine the vibrations coursing through an active centurion. nnI would love to experience them... firsthand.
I'm grateful. You brought back my tutor... ah, that is, the <<1>>.nnI can't believe this happened. We told them to stop and read the runes before they touched anything. nnWe told them!
There's only way to perform proper research.nnWe must study artifacts in the context of their original surroundings.nnKnowledge knows no boundaries!
You've given me reason to improve my skills even further.
Looks like you've given me reason to improve my skills... even further.
The Knights of the Flame will need years to recover from this.
Speak to Warmaster Rahira. You will find her to the east, outside the town's walls.
Many ships now rest at the bottom of our waters.nnWho would risk their lives by staying on a sinking ship?nnThis one thinks this won't end well.
My cousin died. My family decided that it is too dangerous to take his remains to Stonefalls. Like many others, they're taking him to the Velothi Rivergraves. nnNothing good can come of this.
I promise you. I'm not a threat. nnWe aren't really Daedra worshippers. We were poorly trained, and we're obviously not dedicated.nnVonov is the real threat.
Go now. Find the magical wards hidden in houses around town and destroy them.nnWhen you have finished, meet Rahira in the cathedral.
I am pleased to see you again, <<1>>. nnI heard the Hlaalu councilor has you to thank for her life.nnYou're quite a hero, it would seem.
There are too many daedra to make a run for it.
Thanks again for your efforts. With no crew, I'll have to leave this place, but at least the major threat is gone for others should they want to retake the mine.
A big cloud of dust came out of that cave mouth the other day. A bunch of people ran out.
You saved many lives this day. nnMay the moons shine on you, friend.
We didn't think we'd make it past the Daedra. Thank you!
It is of the utmost importance we find out anything about those stolen items.nnPlease, speak to Farah. Convince her to tell us what she knows.
Now that the villagers are safe, it's time to reclaim the Haven.

If you have any questions about my father's stuff, talk to my brother.nnHe told me he'd be off to the west, driving off the Imperials. nnYou tell him to be careful, okay? He thinks he's stronger than he really is.
I am glad we don't have to worry about those filthy ogres anymore. That sure makes my life easier.
You'd better hurry, that bucket leaks like a sieve.
Imperial supply crates are strewn across the beaches to the westnnJust use that kindlepitch I gave you. Burn them. Burn them all!
I can't wait to see my home again. Well, what's left of it.nnWe should do this again sometime! I'll keep the cuffs until then.nnSee you later, brave adventurer!
I know it seems absurd. nnThey're visions from a scroll, but you must trust him, <<1>>. nnWe all must have a little faith.
The old man. He looks disturbed. What's wrong?
Kill Imperial soldiers and use the torch to burn their bodies.nnThose who see their comrades massacred in this way will carry shock and doubt thereafter.
Kill Imperial soldiers. Use the torch to burn their bodies.nnThose who see their comrades destroyed this way will carry their shock and doubt forever.nnThey will never forget their mistake.

I have seen your success. It is written in the scrolls. With the Balac in hand you shall triumph, our enemies vanquished, the Planemeld extinguished!nnDo you understand? The Balac is the key, and you shall find it. Are you willing? Are you ready?
One essential task remains. We must power the wards with the jewels we have charged.nnThen Elden Root will be safe, and we can depart from this wretched place.
<This is unmistakably the body of the lost Altmer mage. It is disturbingly pale and drawn, as if drained. A tome is clutched in its arms.>
Feels like I've got a sack of rocks on my chest. nnBreathing shouldn't be this hard, should it?

You should check to the east. The Imperials are occupying Haven.nnSomewhere in the city, you might find a cowl that would suit Ra'Vashi's needs.nnBring it to this one, so he may disguise himself and learn to blend with the shadows!
Prepare yourself. Whenever you are ready, I can teleport you within the prison.
The <<1>>s are kept within this Palisade. Feed them the fungi, free their minds!
Fill the cups with water from the fountain. nnHurry up! We've got a game to play!
I can't believe the rumors proved true. nnI'll keep my distance from the crypts from here on out.
I can't believe we survived.nnWe owe you so much.
I am glad you made it back safely.

Well, I think you've found all the cows there are to be found. Have you done this before?nnOh. Did you want payment or something? I thought you were just being nice. That's fine then. Go talk to <<1>> back at the pens. He'll give you something.
As soon as everyone is back, we're going to take refuge in Evermore.
Be careful wandering the swamp, stranger.nnThe Peatwalker tribe's totem was stolen. They've turned the spriggans against everyone. They'll attack until it's returned.
Greetings <<1>>. What can I do for you?
Hello again. What can I do for you?
The embers will not harm you
target: they are magic in nature and do not harm the living.

source: Arkay, help us! His fever is higher! What will I do if he dies?
Has Wyress Reinette decided to help us at last?
Gall and pox... those thrice-damned Reach! You won't let them get away with this, will you hero?
You've killed some of these useless beasts, that's for certain. nnMore will appear soon enough. nnI hope the queen hasn't taken ill. That would be a disaster.
Don't worry, you'll get paid. I'm a man of my word!
I've administered my remedy. Now we must attend to her. With any luck she'll be waking soon.
Praise Arkay, you saved her!nnThe Queen would never have had the Minister of War arrested, if things were not so chaotic.
I hope they'll send someone soon....
The ghosts seem to be very agitated. I wonder what's happened to King Eamond that's gotten them upset?
Ghosts are a rarity in this dungeon. I fear for the King.
I must prepare myself. Leave me be.
You made the right choice, <<1>>. I will keep Evermore safe until Queen Arzhela is ready to rule once more.
I won't forget what you've done here today. Thank you.
You! You're alive!nnWhat happened? What's going to happen?
Such commotion. My head hurts so much. I just want it to end, but I'm lingering on and on.
Do my eyes deceive me? nnI have dreamed of this moment.nnMy family is finally safe.

This cult of necromancy is no more than a splintered faction within the Reach. Were it not for the brothers Angof and Brinarch, the Bloodthorn abominations would not even exist. The day those two are dealt with is the day these blasphemies end.
I hope that's not your blood.

The old one should show herself after you defile her shrine. Be wary approaching her. We know too little to separate truth from legend about their kind.nnHagravens often work in concert. There must be others about, although perhaps not right here.
You've done enough already, <<1>>. I will be fine on my own now.nnI wish I could say the same for the rest of my village.

You never know when these altercations might become violent.nnThe taxes will be spent on providing clothing and shelter for the bereaved. I'm surprised that the Bjoulsae Queen's captain isn't more understanding.
Go ahead - use the listening stone, and let's see what these Reach bastards are up to.
You've proven yourself a true champion for Evermore! Lord Alfred knew what he was about when he sent you here.
I'm sure you think you've done what's best for everyone, but I heartily disagree.
The priestess won't listen to me anymore. nnI swear, I have never met such a stubborn servant in all my life.nnI'll make sure the Great Houses hear of her insolence.
Destroy anything and anyone you find on that island.nnThen make them pay for what they've done to the spriggans.

You never know when these altercations might become violent.nnThe taxes will be spent on providing clothing and shelter for the bereaved. I'm surprised that the Bjoulsae Queen's captain isn't more understanding.
Well?
That was wonderful! nnA good race always sends chills up my spine.
Deliver the bag of reagents to Optimate Ostasil. nnYou'll find him in his tower to the north.
An expedient delivery!nnThe stones are in excellent condition.nnFine work.

Now that you're here, we can get on with it. Gabrielle is joining us from the Mages Guild and Darien from the Fighters Guild. I suppose you want to discuss strategy with them. nnWhen you're ready, just ask Gabrielle to open the portal.
We must convince King Eamond's officers that Bangkorai Garrison is ripe for attack. If we retreat, we only allow the enemy to fortify.
We're in your debt. nnI doubt the Ashlander would have spoken to anyone in House Dunmer.
The bodies of our guar lie in the canyon to the south. nnWe need you to recover their harnesses. Kill any scamps that get in your way. Oh, and watch out for lava. nnYou can do it. You're a hero!
Is that my box? You did well to return it. The Reachmen stole it, and I feared what would happened if they opened it.nnThis box contains evil.
What lies unearthed beneath that mountain?
The wailing at the gates has abated. Is this your doing?
What can I do for you, <<1>>?

I will carry Erena's love with me long after I leave, <<1>>. nnIt is because of you I have her strength to carry me.nnI know I should not stay, but I would like to tarry with Erena for a few moments longer.
Goodbye...
Have you completed any contracts for the Fighters Guild yet? I'm counting on you.
<<1>> has a hut in on the sourthern rise overlooking the village. Search her hut. Then take the cure for the affliction.nnThe hut is probably guarded, but hopefully, you can slip past the Kagesh.
It is the very creatures of the forest which turn against me. They are filled with rage, their nature corrupted. Please, I cannot harm them, cannot defend myself. I need help!
The crypts are now warded, but the undead remain. We must deal with them, soon.
We have no time to waste. The bindings weaken even now.
You are skilled, <<1>>. nnIf only you had used such prowess on my behalf....
You should go visit <<1>> if you haven't already. Folk around here say he's as old as the forest itself. Probably not far off, I'd wager.
Ralmas is still examining the cliff racer. I expect to get a report back from him soon. nnIn the meantime, we'll hold our position and wait for reinforcements.
Anis is strong! If he's still alive, he'll make it out okay.nnI'll wait for him here until he returns. Then we'll both travel back to Davon's Watch. nnThey should know what happened to the fort!
I won't raise my hand against a priest of Kynareth, but I cannot disobey my king.
Stenric was wise to choose you. You have done good work.nnOnce you defeated each spirit, it was cast below once more, woefully weak. It will not escape again.
Disgusting, screeching beasts! nnI can hardly hear myself think with all the racket they make. nnHow are my patients supposed to get any rest with those ravenous scavengers soaring overhead?
Do you stand with these knights, or with the Divines?
It is gruesome work, and I do not relish it, but it must be done.nnUse that charm at Bangkorai Garrison. King Eamond will come and destroy the Imperials.
I will have no more dealings with the likes of you.
Hear the words of our Wise-Woman. Accept their truth.
If we heed not the Wise-Woman's tales of our ancestors, we should repeat their mistakes.
I'll have to swing by Norus' tent once I've finished going through these supplies. nnLet's just say I was less than kind when I thought he answered my inquiry about supplies with a joke.
I almost don't know where to start. nnIt's been so long since I had real supplies!
I hope the supplies will last us for awhile.... Between the Orlishkaarn and Mt. Senie, it's a wonder we have anything left.
House Dunmer would keep us penned like kwama.nnWe will not be kept for the amusement of idolators and heretics!
May Saint Veloth bless you and keep you. May your heart be opened to Boethiah.
Edam and his children have long since turned to dust, but their legend remains.
I'm watching you. Touch nothing!
The wind whispers to me tales of distant places, of verdant glades dappled with sunlight. Where is this beauty, this wonder? Why can't I go there?nnWhat is this strange being standing before me?
The remains have vanished from within. Only the stench remains.
When you get close to the door, someone speaks.nn"Don't get so close. You're not done cutting off those ears."
You hear shuffling and coarse whispers coming from inside. After a moment, someone inside speaks. nn"Thanks for feeding us. We need more help, but first, you'll need to prove yourself trustworthy."
You hear shuffling and coarse whispers coming from inside. After a moment, someone inside speaks. nn"Thanks for feeding us. We need more help, but first, you'll need to prove yourself trustworthy."
Captain Renoit attacked us without warning, seeking a cure that didn't exist.nnWe have no cure for the plague, but we do have one for werewolves. nnI just hope we can restore peace again.
Calypsi should be near her tent on the north side of the camp.nnVengeance awaits.
Never liked cliff racers. nnSome of the men thought they were interesting. Worse than cockroaches, I say!
I wish Serjo Ulden would let us attack the heretics at the Shrine. What's he waiting for?
Captain Ondre sent you? That's good news! nnI've been keeping an eye on the Imperial Army. nnI believe we have a chance, so long as we stand united against them.
I'm glad you're still alive, <<1>>.nnAfter all, there's more killing to do.
Through you, Boethiah has granted us victory.nnPraise him... and all our ancestors.
The Imperial ranks break before us. nnIt is time to strike the final blow.
I'm surprised you got anything out of that n'wah. nnIf it were up to me, he'd pay for what happened to the Hortator.
How I wish the Ashlanders would attack the fort! nnThe captain wouldn't order us to retreat. We'd cut them down as they came!nnThat would be... glorious.
Remember your promise. nnIf they won't release me voluntarily, I'll still expect you to do your part.
You tell Gurles it's unkind of him to keep secrets from you. Tell him it's time to let go.
Mr. Kerbol owns the mill. nnHe knows what you need to do now. You have to help those infected soldiers.nnTake those berries to him, and hurry.

It's fortuitous that you arrived when you did.nnWe wouldn't have thought to question the Ashlander, since his kind is frequently stubborn. Ashlanders are prone to telling tales.nnThanks to you, Lieutenant Eris is still alive.

With the king and his mother opposed to each other, neither Sir Dencent nor I can see a clear path.nnYou have no stake in this. We'll abide by your judgment in this matter. nnOur goal is saving Bangkorai from the Imperials. What should we do?
Enter text related to Necris.
Let the Ordinators come! Boethiah has blessed us. What can their pretender-gods do in the face of that?
We're going to strike back, aren't we? Serjo Ulden must intend to strike again!
Most of my fellow soldiers will be quite mad when they return to undeath.nnAt least we gave them a brief respite from their suffering.
Boethiah didn't desert us. nnOur weakness failed him.
You think the Ashlanders are scared? I bet they're real scared.

I suppose you can call yourself a Huntsman now. nnAm I so great a failure? Every ragged traveler who passes this way has found a suitable offering.nnI stand here with bleeding wounds. They're the markings of my inadequacy.
Excellent work, <<1>>! nnThis is going to turn into a bloodbath. I just know it. nnWe've got to get out of here, but not yet. We may be able to use this to our advantage.
See how quickly they take root? Truly amazing.nnWhat mysteries of the deep do they hold for us to discover?
<The king seems much more animated, although his imperious gaze is unnerving. After a moment, he winks at you.>
<You've found Raiyeem's dead body. He's succumbed to his wounds.>
If Garland asked for your services, I'd recommend you finish assisting him.nnDon't worry about us. We'll catch up.

The Dunmer have caught themselves in the anemones of the coral reef.nnWithout proper protection, we can't extricate them from the tentacles' grip.nnThe slime from the sea slugs should protect us from their sting.
I can feel roots shuddering with life.nnThis bleak land will live again. nnCenturies from now, Gil-Var-Delle will know spring.

You must be <<1>>!nnIt's nice to meet you. You seem familiar. Have we met?nnI must apologize if we've met already. My memory has gone all nutwally on me lately. I'm having a hard time remembering a lot of things.
You do realize the danger you're putting us all in, right?nnI can't believe I let Garland talk me into this.
Please, hear my story. Then you can pass this knowledge to our Great Father.nnThen you can say what I cannot.
That looks like enough for a few big fires.nnLook for places where slaves have gathered, and build them a bonfire.
I can't believe there aren't any rats here.nnThere's no water. There's no plants. nnWhy do the Dunmer even live here?
The ones who can find food always try to elicit... services... from those of us who can't.nnI'd sooner die. nnOh, Mara! I'm so hungry.
Want to see a magic trick? Give this one a coin. This one will make it disappear.nnWhat are you looking at? This one said it was a trick....
This affliction the Dunmer are all dying from... this must be a good thing, yes?nnYes! Truly a sending of Khenarthi and Lorkhaj.

I am an educated man. My talents are wasted toiling in fields and mineshafts.nnI brought this to the attention of my so-called "masters." Then they had me beaten.nnDoubtless they were jealous of my superior intellect.
I'm from Blackwood. I'm used to trees overhead and mud underfoot. nnHow can anyone live in a place like this?
Anyone willing to put our lives at risk because of their own selfish goals can't be tolerated.nnIf I have to end his life to save the others, I will.
Ah, <<1>>! We were organizing a counterattack, but events proceeded too quickly. That is to say, you fought them off before we could get there.nnIt appears the journal you found was authentic.
I'm too injured to escape. I'll do what I can to care for any other peasants that the Reachmen capture. Thank you.

I'm glad you both made it back. Josselin and I are  close. I don't think I could lose her after I lost Eamond.nnToo many friends are dying around me, and here I stand with all my powers, helpless.nnExcuse me. I must keep my mind clear and focused.
How is my son? nnDid you give him the antidote?
Whatever you can do to thwart the Imperial's plans will be appreciated. We're stretched way too thin here.
So help is on the way? That's great news.nnI'm trying to help make <<1>> as comfortable as possible, but I'm afraid nursing isn't my strong suit.
I don't have the strength to escape.nnGo on without me.
Leave us.nnMy people must grieve for the many lives lost this day.
You found one of the ghosts?nnWhat did she say?
Show mercy, friend.nnI beg you!
I can't leave until we've rescued the people the Reachmen took captive.nnThere's no telling what they plan to do with us.
I don't have the nerve to try to escape.nnI'd rather live as a slave than risk getting killed.nnGo on without me.
Have you spoken with my father's attendant at the Scarlet Summit? nnIf you're lost, follow the road south. nnMy father's home should be near the top of the hill.
You've found evidence? Excellent! nnPlease take your evidence and a warrant to <<1>>. nnIrano has so many men and mer under his sway. He's the only one I trust over there.

I used to see <<1>> every day to file my complaints. Since I never had evidence, she started refusing to speak with me.nnHer father never asked me for proof. He trusted my word.nnBaylan is still green. He's playing by the book.
I don't have the nerve to try to escape. nnI'd rather live as a slave than get beaten again.nnGo on without me.
I'm sure <<1>> is waiting for any information you and Barnabe could get. It took us quite a while to return with our prisoner.
You've learned nothing from me, <<1>>. Nothing!nnYou'll be hunted by the Imperial Army for the rest of your unnaturally short life.

<You've found a body. The feverish addict is barely moving.>nn<His glassy eyes stare off into space, as if witnessing something too great to comprehend. >nn<Although he's alive, he doesn't respond to your presence.>
<<1>> will be very interested to hear what you got the prisoner to tell you.nnWe'll send him to the dungeon in Evermore for now.
I was there when King Eamond died. He was mad with pain and spoke his last words to <<1>>.nnI should have saved him. Evermore needs him now more than ever.
Unless you are here about contracts, I have guild business to attend to.
