You have seen it with your own eyes.nnYour fort spreads this poison, but I will stop it. nnI will not see it fall into the hands of another unsuspecting soul, even if I have to burn your fort to the ground.
I hope you found my sister.

I saw the Ashlanders chase the Ordinators out to their camp. I - I was too afraid to approach them. They looked angry. I didn't want them to think I was on the side of the Ordinators.nnI hope they can put the saltrice to good use.

To think he was right! He was watching our neighbors all the time.nnThe next time people move into the Rilvayns' old home, I'll almost feel sorry for them.nnAfter all, he'll think his spying is justified.
Shavari is relieved you took care of the matter.nnThis one does not like to think about what was inside the chest.nnThis one doesn't like to think that it's out now.
If they catch us, they'll sacrifice us.nnI'll stay here and take my chances.

Were my instructions not clear? Break Ogambu's equipment, and kill the worthless churls she experiments on. When she notices and investigates, kill her.nnFleshlings excel at breaking and killing, do they not?
You can't prosper without angering a few people along the way. nnI would say we should swap stories, but that might make both of us accomplices.nnHa! That's a joke, of course!
I'm sorry. I'm very tired.nnWhy don't you go back and talk to that Dremora? If she wasn't there before, I'm sure she's there now.
Once you get the bark, throw it on the embers. nnWe'll infuse it with the cure while it burns.

Virgil finally told me the truth after I sent you to find Agnes.nnThere's a cure for this plague, but I'd rather die than receive it.nnI'm glad you set him free. I couldn't disobey orders, but there's nothing to be gained by slaughter.
You helped the soldiers who were infected? Good.
I knew something was up when the scouts didn't report back. What will happen to us now?
I worry for Virgil.nnI don't think the soldiers would mistreat him, but in this climate of fear and distrust, who knows?nnHurry to Agnes. If she's not back yet, she will be soon.
Perhaps later, we can get to know each other a little better.nnWe've been far too formal.nnOf course, I'd offer you a lower rate, since you've been so helpful.
Agnes Mavine knows where the cure is. I'm certain of it.

Renoit has no idea what he's done.nnHe holds my brother captive. He insists we have a cure, but it's not what he thinks.nnWhen the soldiers attacked, these people defended themselves. Soldiers were bitten. I was too. Now we'll all become werewolves.
Ferise and I go back a long time. I'm a bit hurt she thought I would not understand. I will have to buy her something nice to celebrate.
I must return to our outpost.nnI must tell the others of our deeds.nnYour name will be sung in our praises around the fire for many days.
Is she dead? What happened?
I heard about Serjo Belaal. Such a shame.nnShe will be missed terribly.
Distasteful rumors are spreading about Serjo Belaal's death. nnI am certain no one of taste or breeding would pay attention to them.
Thank the Eight. You have the book.nnYou've proven yourself, my friend. I'm sorry I didn't trust you.
Oh! What to do!
Have you been able to find anything out?nnWhoever's controlling the orcs, I'd wager they're deep in these root caves.
I'm supposed to bring Lady Belaal's meal upstairs. nnI don't want to do it. She'll... she'll....nnGo away! I can't talk to you!
One of the servants claimed to hear a shocking din from upstairs.nnFortunately, he is known to be mentally defective.nnHave you preserved Navalie's honor, <<1>>?
They ready themselves for battle. We will hold the palace while you take out the Imperial within.nnWe must all move quickly.
Together, we will return Bangkorai to its true rulers.
After you freed us, my egg-sister met as at the Redoran manor. nnShe said she would get us home to Black Marsh.nnIt's been many months since I've seen home. I wonder if it's still underwater....
We've made it, <<1>>!nnI'm free of that prison forever!
I've been praying for your safe return.nnDid you manage to collect enough wormwood blossoms?
I saw several of our egg-brothers running from the canyons.nnI knew I would find you here.
Kill the risen! nnLead them home.

The earth is old in this land. It's cracked and brittle. It bleeds red at the slightest touch.nnIn many places where the earth has gone to rot, the mud is yellow and clotted.nnHow I miss the good mud of homeland: black as night, and fine as silk.
You're welcome in my house, stranger. nnI'll turn no one away in these times, save those who wish me and mine violence.

You're a wanderer, aren't you? Have you come far? What have you seen? Did - did you see the ocean? Is it really as big as they say?nnI haven't been beyond this valley. Not since I was an infant, anyway. And only once to Vivec's Antlers.
Imperials, Bretons, Khajiit... those outsiders aren't just our enemies. They're inferior. nnI don't understand why House Father Aryron shows them any mercy.
Serjo Violyne is a very nice young lady. She's always polite and elegantly noble.nnSometimes, though, you can see her look away to the west as the sun goes down. She looks sadder than Saint Meris.
What sort of monster keeps a mother from her child? nnIf he doesn't reunite us, tell him I'll cast myself into this well!
I don't know why Rosamund wants wood. nnI just thought she'd like it if I helped. Maybe she'll be grateful. It's been a long time since I...nnAh! Here's a piece that's not too burned!
This was such a quiet place until the slave revolts started.nnWhat a shame. I miss the peace and quiet.
This is really quite a dull place. nnDay in, day out, there is only routine. nnWork. Pray. Eat. Sleep.

My dear husband is getting on in years. He's been a good provider, but now he's entirely too tolerant of heresies.nnThis Ebonheart Pact has weakened our people. nnIt's made them too ready to accept the ways of the n'wah outsiders.
My life will never be what it was, but I'll raise our daughter to be as great a warrior as her mother.
Vusara should be in the barracks to the east. nnTake the charm there. Use it on her.nnMy end draws near. Please bring word of my fate to <<1>>.
If you can help liberate the city, we'll all be in your debt.nnGods be with you, my friend.
Have you completed any contracts for the Fighters Guild yet? I'm counting on you.
What can I do for you, <<1>>?
Did you get the samples?
Greetings <<1>>. What can I do for you?
I wanted to thank you again for saving my business.nnWith the profits from this sale, I should be able to hire some mercenaries.nnThen I can protect my next batch of workers!
Were you able to find my children?nnI know Danea will need help bringing her brothers back.
The cave is to the east. You can see the path from here. nnPlease, find the urn and destroy it.
Hm? Oh, it's you. nnWere you able to fix the lamps? nnNo trouble, I hope?

I was hesitant to lead my troops into dangerous odds, yet it appeared unavoidable. nnThe amulets you provided will save many lives. nnWhen we return to Elden Root victorious, your assistance will be properly recognized.
Come one step closer, and I'll cut out that lying tongue of yours.
You've returned. nnHave you fought back the tide in the grove?
Thank you again for the amulets.
Thank you again for retrieving the effigies.nnI wish we had never seen those accursed statues!
You've done us a fine service. I won't forget that.
Are you still seeking the bounties? I hope many have fallen at your hands.

My father must have drawn that picture from memory. nnHe couldn't get close to me, not when he was in rags and I was in finery. He still got every detail right. Even the way my nose turns up on the end.nnHe was a good artist... and a good man.
Thank you, <<1>>. nnYou've brought us peace by freeing us. nnYou've reunited us, so our spirits can finally rest.
The mountain's smoking again. It does that a lot now. nnWe heard that Mount Senie erupted. I wonder if volcanoes can catch eruptions like we catch colds? nnOne "sneezes," and the next one catches it.
I've never kept my destination secret. nnI'm basically passing through on my way to Elsweyr. It's the last of the real frontier kingdoms.

I'm glad to see a fellow traveller. The roads east aren't safe anymore. nnIf it's not the plague, it's lava flows. If it's not the lava flow, it's Ashlanders. If it's not the Ashlander? Cliff racers.nnUgh. I hate cliff racers.
When you're ready to start the ritual, scatter the dust over the gravesites I've prepared.
A "1"? Hah!nnYou better roll again, because you're not going to win with a "1."
Hello again, <<1>>.nnI don't know about you, but I'm going to kill a few more and call it a day.
Might I sing you a song, my lady? Can I tell you a tale? nnWe could take a private room. I've been told I have a silver tongue.
Shall I dance for you, my lord? I've studied under many masters of the art. nnI'm sure I could hold your attention for hours.
Do you have the poison?
All right, that's a round of scuttle, two plates of fried netch, one without butter....
Now that you've settled my great-grandfather's spirit, you should be able to talk to him.
Enough talk. I need another mazte. nnWhere's that serving girl? By B'vec, she's useless!nnMedaren needs to buy more help.

This plague that's been spreading... I think it'll be good for Stonefalls! nnIt's been too long since something came through and culled the weak.nnThere's no plague in Kragenmoor. Have you noticed that? nnWe're not weak.
Krothag is warrior-born and honorable.nnRemind him of his obligation to the other troops, even if he has no love left for me.
I just came back from a trip Davon's Watch. nnIt's strange to see grass again!

The Dres are big talkers, but they're as weak and feminine as the Altmer. nnAll their hard work is done by slaves. They say it saves the nobles time for more "worthy pursuits."nnI guess lying about and eating gorapples is more "worthy" than working.
You need to find that antidote.nnGet it to <<1>> and <<2>> before it's too late!
You've helped me regain my freedom and get a little payback.nnI can't thank you enough!
The Gutter's filled with trash. nnWhat a waste of walking skin.
That sword was not meant to be found, especially not by the Imperial army.nnWe really need to recover it and hide it away for good. I'm counting on you.

In my father's day, House Dres' soldiers fought the snake-men of Akavir.nnNow we're in the Gutter, fighting skooma peddlers and escaped slaves.nnI should have been stationed in Cyrodiil, fighting over the Imperial throne. That's where the glory is!

You can count on fourth things: war, taxes, the birth of inferior people, and the endurance of the Tribunal.nnUnless you count each Tribunal member separately, course... then there would be six things!
The tale of Saint Aralor teaches us that even the foulest criminal can repent and begin anew.nnWe must remember this when we redeem the lost souls of the Gutter.
The road to Heimlyn Keep begins just north of Kragenmoor. Then it curves around to the east.nnI fear for the safety of the garrison. I hope <<1>> allows them to leave before the volcano erupts.
Already, Imperial necromancers have stolen the bodies and souls of our honored dead.nnThey must pay for this atrocity ... in blood!
Mara bless you for helping these people. They don't have anyone else to turn to.nnJust don't get yourself killed, all right?
Have you said your devotions to the Three today? nnWhy don't you go do that right now?nnWe can talk later.
I led a caravan to Davon's Watch earlier in the month. What a waste of time!nnThe docks are shut down, and nearly everyone has barricaded themselves in their homes.
You are not the first novice smith who's petitioned to become my apprentice. nnYou will not be the first I turn away, either.nnShow me your work. I will judge it and decide if you belong at my forge.
How are you still standing? nnI'm sorry! I meant nothing by that! Forget I was here. Forget you ever saw me.nnPlease, don't hurt me!
Thank you for helping me. nnI only wish there was more we could do to aid the afflicted.
My men didn't deserve to suffer for my mistakes.nnThank you for helping free them from the curse.

The parts, the pieces. That's all of them. That's everything you need.nnGo to the heart of the works. Heal the mechanisms. Nothing will work until you do. We can't rest yet.nnBut be careful. Be oh so careful. My brothers tried to fix it. They died.
Take the ingredients to Felen's scrying pool.nnSwirl them among the herbs in the blessed water.nnHe will see what he needs most.

You! I remember you. After you delivered that letter, I found out my sister is dead.nnI think an experiment went wrong, and one of those beasts killed her.nnNow I've devoted myself to finding her killer. One day, I'll avenge her.
Maybe I can convince the living runecrafters to continue my experiments....
The enemies will open portals in distant places, far from observers, so that they avoid the wrath of armies.nnWe may need all the help we can get to seal the rifts.
Thank you. I feel much better. Hurry and deliver the antidote to my mother. I fear for her life.
You are not permitted to leave until <<1>> is done with you.
The <<1>> has something to show Master Tree-Paws?
What have you brought me?
A novice runecrafter, are you? Excellent.nnThere is much I can teach you. Let's see your work.
So much time wasted...
There's still plenty of pudding left! Don't be shy, dear.nnYou can take as much as you like.
The other champions are ready. Are you?
Are you ready to train in the fine art of runecrafting? nnYou've got the soul of an artist buried deep inside you. I can tell.
Ready to start learning the ways of forestry? nnFrom little acorns, great trees grow.
Are you ready to learn about outfitting?nnYou've got a lot of skinning ahead of you, but you seem sharp enough.
Grab a hammer and hit the forge.
All finished with the nix-hounds, then? Praise to Boethiah!nnYou should talk to <<1>>, our most most elder guar-herd. He's outside the gates of our village to the south.
The soldiers who didn't head into Gil-Var-Delle moved to the northwest. nnI heard they're building a fortress there.nnYou should be able to find our stolen rings there.
Finish that damned woman off and put her head on a pike for me, would you?nnIf I could only see her face as you drain the life out of her body. Such wonderful thoughts.
It seems you were able to dispatch the daedric nobles while Arafel closed the rift, at last.
Your help with those crystals was timely. Thank you again.
Gurles' administers his best medicine, and yet our princess fares no better. What are we to do?
You should not pity them. Pity is a weakness.nnIf they had won, do you think they would feel pity for us?

With the ordinators defeated, we've sent word to our tribe's conclave. We're short of food.nnI pray they can spare a guar for slaughter. nnThe last we heard, the nix-hounds we taking a heavy toll on the herds.
Are you familiar with Bosmer forestwalking? nnPaths wind through the treetops. It's easy to cross large distances by walking along them.
Have you seen the Warden Master? nnShe's near the healing huts, north of here.
I've spent my life fighting Daedra.nnThe thought of summoning one intentionally makes my skin crawl. nnI hope we won't regret this.
Welcome back to the docks, my friend.nnLife has returned to normal, thanks to you.
Ancestor's Landing is situated along the coast, north and west of here.nnMeet us there... and take care!
Prove to the other captains that the claims against the king were a hoax.nnThen we'll stop this riot.
Assuage my fellow captain's suspicions, and the riots will cease.nnYou have my word.

Did the guards send you to kill me? If you're thinking you've found a sea-battered old captain, you're mistaken. nnI'll hang your corpse from the yardarm to warn other assassins.nnHave at you! Stand and deliver!
Jahi and <<1>> will adjust to life in the city quickly. And the sooner I find a buyer, the sooner we can put this all behind us.
The Withered Hand wants to sabotage our ships.nnI'll make sure the king hears about this!nnHopefully, he'll let me march a group of guards onto the docks.
The throne keepers are pious, devout men... but they're no match for an army of skeletons.nnThey desperately need your help.

General Thoda is a trusted advisor and a good friend. He has heard the rumors about the Withered Hand, and he can help us.nnTell no one else though. People remember Suturah, and hearing his sons have returned could cause a panic.
So they attacked Ilmaha as well, eh?nnThank you for taking care of them.
To know the prince lives is a great relief. I never would have forgiven myself were he harmed.

I'm tempted to say I'm sorry you became caught up in all this, but something tells me it was the hand of fate that brought you here. nnBesides, if we can't stop them from stealing the Ansei Wards, none of us are safe.
Everytime I feel we've come closer to peace, something happens to force us to take a step backwards. <<1>> must be spoken to.
For centuries, amateurs like yourself have tried to release me. Fools! All of you!nnYou'd have a better chance of becoming the next emperor.
Thank you again, friend. You saved my life back there and with my life, you saved many.

Isn't it pleasant up here? It's far above the dust of the streets, the air is cooler  between you and me, I think that's why mages build towers. Smart, huh?nnSo, did you come up here for the atmosphere or do you have business with the guild?
Is it true the Kothringi are all dead now? When I was young, I used to visit their villages.
Is it true the Kothringi are all dead now? When I was young, I used to visit their villages.
Is it true the Kothringi are all dead now? When I was young, I used to visit their villages.
My father says that my Devad will do us an evil turn. But what evil could dwell in so fair a temple?nnIs he not as a dream? Oh, I should spend a fortnight pondering the slope of his brow!

The liquor is where I'll really clean up. A village full of people who've never enjoyed real spirits? They'll take to it like moths to a flame. And once they do, well....nnSome of them won't be able to stop. But that's only because they're weak.
You are welcome among us, though we do not know you as sister. We will aid you if the Nest-Mother wills it.
I do not know where the other Ansei Wards have been taken, but Tu'whacca tells me that you must go east, my friend.nnHe says that is the next step on your journey.
You should really kill that <<1>> over there.
I didn't want to steal. They made me do it!
Have you discovered what perverts the shrine?
Whatever you learned from the spirits, take it to Telenger. I've no time for you right now.
What have you found from your search?
What do they want with us?
I do not like the looks of this....
More spirits? I thought you were leading us to safety.
By Onsi I hate monkeys.
I cannot believe my ears... how can this be? Good <<1>> - these phantoms cannot have their way. Do not give in! We must make a stand!
Ayvas is a great prophet. And you are a liar.nnYou'd better leave our village... heretic.
There's one fewer monster in this valley.nnIt would be easier if I could ask you to kill the other one as well. But I don't think you'd be able to recover my daughter's heart from his gut.
Not all of them abandoned me.nnFaith is a strange power. A terrible burden that grants the power the endure any weight.
<The spirit stares right through you.>
I will take care of these people until they are fit for travel.  You are owed many thanks.
Don't even think about it! If you try to pick me up and give me a kiss, I'll bite your nose off!nnI may look like a monkey, but I'm not a monkey, and I'm done being treated this way!
Make those deliveries and Unishi will undo what has been done.
How may I help?
So you found them? The news shall make this day bearable. You've done good work for us today. I won't forget it.
If you're serious about this, the  <<1>>'s lair is in the cave northwest of here. You can see it from here by looking through the gates.
Did <<1>> speak with you?
I'm certain <<1>> is in the Town Hall. She is always very involved in her duties and rarely leaves.
So you found Rinlan? Why is he not back?nnWhatever nonsense has consumed him, I hope he finishes with it soon... for his sake.
I'm trying to arrange a peaceful end to this. Running around and killing the other side's negotiators is not helping!

I doubt my assistants are willing to row all the way to Mournhold. I suppose I must wait for my ships to be retrieved.nnI've had my fill of the stench of the swamp. After this expedition is complete, I plan to retire to more scholarly studies.
Another able hand to aid Sentinel!nnWe are two of a kind.
Thank you for bringing one of those rats to justice.
You saved two lives today. I couldn't have gone on without this stubborn brute.nnI owe you everything.
We Ash'abah owe you much.
I smell a great burning.nnYou succeeded, yes?
<Marimah is dead.>
Welcome, Dark One. Our work continues on the search for your prize, and we have brought many fresh supplies for your work.nnWhat can this humble servant of the Worm Cult do for you?
target: Welcome, Dark One. Our work continues on the search for your prize, and we have brought many fresh supplies for your work.nnWhat can this humble servant del Culto del Verme do for you?

source: The servants of Bogmother grow with her rage. Yet the Archeins continue their corpsetrading with the necromancers.nnYou must not let these meetings continue. The Bogmother has shown her wrath. Give their bodies to the soil.

I'll mark the graves' locations on your map. I'd go with you, but I have to watch and ensure they don't slip by.nnThere are other Ash'abah who can join you, though. You want one skilled in swordplay, or one who's adept at restoration magic?
Ring the herder bell near one of the goats to herd it this way. They know they should be with me

You have proven yourself Tu'whacca's champion. You will recover the other Ansei Wards.nnBy breaking the wards on this sanctum, you've re-opened the hidden tunnel I used to escape. If you wish a quick exit, use the secret exit to my right.

Ah, you found it! I wasn't able to make much progress while you were gone, but this should make all the difference. nnDeciphering these runes may take some time. Please don't feel obligated to stay, but check back with me in a little while.
Thank you for ridding our Hist of the shalk. I hope to avoid future invading pests such as those.
You have Dar'Thid's thanks for avenging his mates.
Now that the flies have been release, it's our time to attack! Please aid is in the battle!
I'm not sure how you survived, but next time you won't be so lucky.
You have already done great things for us, <<1>>. It is only right that you lead the Cult of the Fang.
I'm saddened that I have yet to hear anything. I miss my days as an active trader.
Despite <<1>>'s objections, I think those new members are going to work out well. Nice work.
I don't have the nerve to try to escape. I'd rather live as a slave. Go on without me.
J'Derr and Dar'Virr will never forget what you've done for them. If you ever need a fast ship on a dark night, you know where to find this one, no?
Our strength grows with your aid.
Is it finished? Did you kill Inerri?
You've done me and many others a great service today that will not be forgotten. We've experienced so many who wish us harm that you've been a refreshing reminder that good is still out there.
News of your victory has spread throughout the camp. We will prosper under your leadership.
I can hardly believe this is real. So much has transpired.... Forgive me, dear friend, I am overwhelmed with emotion.
We should not have left her behind. Lorkhan's breath! There had to be another way....
Telenger appears quite adversely affected by today's events. Why don't you speak with him? I believe it would provide him some degree of comfort.

Ahmuzi wishes you luck.nnThis one understands their frustrations, but all we do is attempt to protect their lives. Sure, we could give them  boats, but they would soon be swimming with dreugh if they tried to flee.nnMaybe if we could just calm them.
Excellent work. Now, find <<1>>. He should be toward the heart of the camp by the waterfall.
If you ever need a fast ship on a dark night you know where to find me.
I never should've listened to <<1>>. Look at all the trouble he's caused!
You have to find Soradenor, he'll know what to do! You should be able to find him up by the ruins!
Do what you must. Ghasaaj will not interfere.nnThis one will merely say you were... helping the guard. Yes, that's it.

I hope the prince has learned more. I believe the Withered Hand has brought one of the Ansei Wards here, and that does not bode well.nnYou were at Tu'whacca's Throne, were you not? So you know that as well as anyone.
You beat me, <<1>>.  I will follow your lead from here on out.  Do not fail us.
I'm still shaking from all of this, but I have to look after Venosir now.
Hurry up! Untie me! Help me escape!
Move along. Do not crowd the entrance.
You must go quickly. I  am fading much faster than I expected. My fate, and the fate of all Alik'r I fear  is in your hands.

If you truly wish to help, I may know where the remedy is held.nnThe military has crates of medicine for their own. I know not how you plan on getting your hands on them, but if you did... you would save the life of my son.
I trusted both Hjarl and Keira with my life. To know one of them threw away all we've accomplished pains me more than these shackles ever will.

I must apologize if I seem agitated.nnThe people of this Harbor are in a situation I would not wish on any. We have been here for weeks now and all we have accomplished is to lose our troops in the jungles.
Whatever the Minister asked you to do, please do so quickly. This town is on the verge of a riot.
The first dose is always the hardest. See how peaceful his face is now?nnYour Orc female should find her way out of the mine. I would follow her, unless you've changed your mind about staying.
I wonder if it's too late too late to change my mind.
Are they gone? Have they stopped attacking for now?
Nice job! We've stopped the werewolves for the time being. Go let the townsfolk know they're safe for now.
By Oblivion's gates, save me.nnI could stab you right now. I really could.
Have you found anything we can use?
You have our eternal thanks.
If you want to discover what <<1>>'s favorite student gave him, you must speak with the servants of <<2>>.
These mementos will help me cope with this loss. One day, I hope to forget all this. For now I'm going to hide out here, try to ride out the storm.
Go, go! There's no time to be standing around talking while the food gets cold.nnGet out there and deliver this stuff!
Keep your head down!nnWhat are you doing here?
This land will be reclaimed, but it has a long way yet to go.
Teeus and Shade-Tail have been invaluable for staying a step ahead of the authorities. Without the two of them, I fear we may be in for hard times.
You have served your people well, <<1>>. I only wish we could have one like you come from every hatching.
I called an arbiter here to decide my fate, but she wished to speak to you first.nnWhatever she decides, I will submit to. It is the only justice I can give to the ones I've wronged.

Not all withstand a proving such as you faced. I believe you will one day be renowned as a great champion among our people, <<1>>.nnGo now and meet the masters of <<2>>. They will have much for you to do.
What are you waiting for?
In the next hatching, we shall name one of the designated Hunters in honor of your deeds, <<1>>.
Completed the rite, have you? The students usually look more taxed when they come down from the tower. Perhaps I've underestimated you.
Oh please tell me you were able to find them... and in one piece!
The wind carries your name to every ear, <<1>>. You've done many things to enrich the next hatching.nnHave you spoken with the Hatch Keeper, <<2>>?
Who could stand by while the Nagas slaughter and steal like a flock of cliff racers?nnNo, we must be mountains before the spring gales. We must shove their anger aside like the empty air.

Have you watched a Dunmer in the rain? They flinch like nervous birds.nnA Saxhleel lets the rain pass over him as he lets the air. As he lets the mud and the roots. It's all the same, really, if you know how to look at it.
I hope you were able to speak with <<1>>. The madness and the deaths are heavy burdens to bear. I hope he's coping as well as I am.
I've had enough of your accusations, outsider! I'll hear nothing more until I speak with <<1>>.
Thank you for having the strength to do what needed to be done.
There is no time for talk. You must find a way to put an end to this. My blades can do nothing.
I've seen a lot of new faces lately. I've heard Keethius is not too pleased about the people who have joined recently.
I hope those fires weren't some sort of witchlight sorcery. But I did notice the gas is gone....nnIt could be a trap. Another trick perhaps? Another lie?

Thank Onsi! I don't have much time, stranger. Hearken to my words of warning.nnWe were attacked by a Withered Hand army led by the necromancer <<1>>. The army has withdrawn, but he's not done with Tava's Blessing yet.
That's some nice equipment. Maybe you should leave before we take it from you, eh?
I hope you've had some luck out there.
I will kill any orcs that try to escape, then meet you at the other side of the lake.
Would you help me with one last thing?
You thought as the disciple did, though I am sure she is conflicted.
They didn't take long.nnIf there's one thing pirates know, it's how to be fast and brutal.
Was he very cross? He has never raised a hand to me, but I still fear his wrath. Did he... say I was free to leave?
I'm not the one you need to talk to now. <<1>> is down in the basin, hiding out on the island. Whatever you found, take it up with him.
Y'ffre walk with you, <<1>>.
My vengeance is satisfied. Vardishal will have my aid.
Thank you for visiting Satakalaam. I hope all is well in that place.
I've always hated atronachs, even when I was alive. Worthless creatures.

Thanks to you, the Withered Hand now has one less necromancer to increase its forces.nnOur mission here is complete. I can reconvene with <<1>>, and we can start discerning the location of the Ansei Wards.
We've learned a lot from you.
Thanks to your training, I'll be much better prepared when we see real combat.

When you need us, we will come. I don't know what use we can be. Maybe I can distract them with stories about how it was in my day.nnOr Xoqui can throw up on them. Who knows. Maybe they'd slip on the vomit and hit their head on a rock.
Good luck, <<1>>. May the guards always be looking the other way.
Have you found what I sent you for? Anything of hers?
I'm glad you found Ritresse now to deal with the Maormer!
I take it the amulets worked, judging by those that came running here.
Well done!

I see you have gathered the runes as promised.nnNow, you must place them on their proper altars.nnSpeak to each of the scholars. Hear their words. Take in their knowledge and place the runes where you feel they belong.
My apologies. My fellow guards have informed that you're an actual living being.
Already I feel the spirits of my companions fade.nnFinally, my friends will travel to where they truly belong.
The jars of Hist sap I saw were in the center of the pirate camp, to the west. That hilltop with the torches on it.nnIt's surrounded by pirates. It won't be easy to get to.
You chose that arrogant cur over me? You will come to regret that my friend and you won't be the only one.
Casnar and I will see each other soon, thanks to you. I am sure he will craft a poem in your honor or some such.
You let her chose that worm over me? I should challenge your honor for this...but she is just one woman. There are others. Maybe it is for the best.
By the Eight, aid has arrived! Please tell me you're here to help. Things here at our farms couldn't be worse.
Oh, it's you! Been a while, yeah? You know, that altruistic streak is bound to get you in trouble one of these days. Can't just go around helping everyone, y'know?
Do you have the reagents I require?
It appears you have all you need. If you are succesful, this will be a day <<1>> remembers forever.

I have witnessed many dark crimes in my time as Justice, but they pale in comparison to this.nnTo think our own Magistrate would make a deal with the Withered Hand. What could she possibly hope to gain from such a thing?
What have you decided?
Ahh. I can feel my blood pumping faster.nnTime for a nap.
I came here to cure a fever.nnI don't think lying out here on the hot rocks is making me feel any better.
Elennae is adept at creating illusory projections of herself. She created one to escort me out here and help direct help. Look for it across the tree bridge just to the southwest of here.
Maybe this trip was a mistake.
It worked! Let us head back at Telenger's camp so we can bring him the good news!nn...I hope that Meliara does not try to take credit for our achievements.
My knees are a bit stiff. I hope you don't mind if I don't stand to greet you.

I admit, it was only after talking to Lei-Kai did I have a true change of heart about Riane. I thought... it was my only option.nnI understand that she will never forgive me. Perhaps I will never forgive myself.
The dead boar is wearing a decorative collar. Faded symbols adorn the fur. Its throat is slit, and patches of dried blood can still be seen on the surrounding ground.
Delicious bones. Much marrow!nnHarpies thank <<1>> for this meal. Yes.
My heart burns when I think on what those ogre beasts did to my father! Remember, if you have need aid just call and the ancestor's spirits will come to aid you!
Greetings to you, stranger.
Everything is blurry. How can the desert feel this cold?
The flames have returned to their expected yellow-orange.
Have you found any treasure? It's not so difficult, just a case of keeping alert and defending yourself down there. Anyone as brave as you shouldn't have any problem...
Aha! It looks like your treasure hunt has been a success. Come, show me what you've found.
They're all dead, aren't they? The poor things.nnMay Morwha care for their souls.
You were supposed to avenge my wife, not bring her back to me! Now she will torment me endlessly, now what am I to do?nnPoor, poor Jarakhad...
I hope those reports keep the Archeins and Wardens fighting eachother for a good long while.
Wait, where is the crown? You gave it to Telenger yourself? You betrayed me?nnI cannot believe this! Did Elennae put you up to this?

The Stablemaster was careful always to have a full crate of scorpion venom antidote in his dwelling. If you search the buildings near the stables it should not be hard to find.nnOnce you have that you will be able to aid my poor lost horses.
I must rest.nnAlready I feel the life drain from my body.nnMy time... has finally come.
Cursed, I tell you. These lands are cursed. The desert belongs to the dead.nnRuptga sent the beetles as a sign. They'll just keep coming, more and more beetles  until we leave.
If I can take down a couple of the weak ones....nnI think I'd just feel better.
I'll be fine. Just have to keep swallowing. To keep from- urp!
Greetings again, friend, did you succeed in your quest to find the spine cactus plants?
Disappearances and deaths have taxed the city greatly, but people will rest easier knowing the killer has been caught.
Did the magistrate agree to release me?
You have nothing for me. Stop drawing attention to me.
You have returned! Please tell me you found something.
I wonder how long we're going to stay out here?
I will prevent the necromancer from drawing on his full power while you infiltrate his cave and eliminate him. His powers should be diminished somewhat.
I'm worried that you'll rush after Shiri unprepared.nnPromise me you'll fetch Tu'whacca's Gift from HoonDing's Watch first.

Thank you for the help, <<1>>!nnI apologize for my appearance. The necromancer's first attack was more brutal than expected, before we were prepared to fend off his minions.nnMeliara may have some spell to assist, but I would rather heal naturally.
We must regroup and recuperate before launching another assault.nnThen we'll wipe the vermin from Zehtswater Cave for good!
Go east to Relazar's quarters. He is waiting for us within.nnAll you need do is keep him distracted until I arrive with <<1>> and <<2>>.

You must send these criminals back to the abyss they crawled out of! They evil they comitted in life has made them powerful in death.nnI have no power to act here, so you must act for me. You must taunt them into attacking you and then destroy them!
A very sad thing, Penitent <<1>>. My followers Anamara and Hram have both chosen to leave our fold. I can't think why
That was incredible! You crushed those hideous things!nnIf it's not too much trouble, now that you've saved me from being eaten  could you please untie me? I must escape this awful cave.
You look like an able sort. I need someone to track down and deliver a letter to a man named <<1>>.

<<1>>! I hoped I would find you here. Your help is needed once again.nnSatakalaam is overrun with Withered Hand and their undead minions. But there are still survivors. We cannot in good conscience ignore their plight.

Speak to everyone that is willing.nnI would say to look for the suspicious ones first, but, well... they all seem to fit that description currently.nnIf you find out anything, anything at all, please return to me at once.

Hey, don't pester me anymore; you got all that you're going to get out of me.nnWord of advice though, stranger. Valaydia doesn't like people asking questions around here. You might want to remember that.
I... am astounded she has graced us with her presence. Words fail me. Please, <<1>>, will you speak on my behalf?
Ah, <<1>>. You aquired a disguise. It's quite becoming on you.nnYou bear an unusual power. The waves of it crash over me.nnWhat did you find in the necromancers' cave?
Go. Tell <<1>> I will stand with him. I'm sure he'll be pleased.

Ironically, it was in our fight against the hideous goblins that we came to love the desert and its simple beauty.nnNow you must face the proud Orc warriors of ancient Orsinium. The fight for the Orc city proved to be one of our greatest trials.
Thank you for finding those eggs. I've been worrying myself sick about the consequences of our foolish actions.
You'll find the dreugh matrons in the sea caves along the coast and outer islands. They tend to lay their eggs there as well, though you may find some elsewhere.
Ha ha, look at the little rats go! Run little one, run!

Have you burnt their boats yet? You'll find the rowboats spread along the shore. Be careful, they'll probably have a few pirates guarding them.nnWhen you're finished meet me by the Captain's tent near the beach.
I love living here. It's so peaceful. I have no cares or worries. Who could ask for more?
I would have paid all the silver I would ever earn for the rest of my life to have seen his face when he opened the urn! Ha!
I ordered that last glimmerwine a while ago. I wonder what's taking so long.
I heard you've been trying to find a villager who went missing. Since you helped me, I'll give you some advice. You should abandon your investigation. Some things happen for a reason.

So, the fool is dead. How fitting he drained his own wards to try and save his pathetic life. His soul will not find rest. I will make sure of it.nnNow, my mortal friend, what shall I do with my wayward children?
You'll find the dreugh matrons in the sea caves along the coast and outer islands. They tend to lay their eggs there as well, though you may find them elsewhere.
Thanks again for helping me. Now that Captain Ravenil's men are distracted, I still have a chance.nnYou've earned my trust, if you're interested I'd like your help with the treasure.
Destroy her.nnDestroy her for everything that she has done to these people. It is not right... not right at all.
Search the cave atop the ledge. With any luck you'll find the troll up there.
I'm tired of talking to strangers about things that are none of their concern. Please leave me be.
It looks like this is the end. Thank you for trying to help me.
What I should do is get rid of Harus and promote you, instead. Have you considered a career as a constable?
I can't believe it! You risked your life and gave me the credit.
Your contribution will impact Saxhleel for generations to come. Our people thank you.

The people of the bazaar turn hostile, and very ugly. Do not worry, you will see soon.nnWhen Ma'Zarman was heading this way, this one stumbled across some interesting cargo that the merchants hid.nnBlood and poison? Why would they need that?
I hear that you are being honored by the elder. nnI hope you can find it in yourself to treat their honor with respect, Dark Elf.

They're honoring YOU? I've been studying them for years. Apparently they respect brute force more than careful study.nnAt least a fellow Dunmer gets to participate. Maybe I will get to in the next hatching.
We must recover the blades of the Ansei.nnIf we don't, Alik'r may fall victim to the scourge of necromancy!
Ah, just the one I've been waiting for. You had several chances to abandon this crazy search but you just couldn't let it go.
I cannot tell you where the necromancer children are, for I do not know. Even so, you may be the only person who can recover the Ansei Wards.nnMay our ancestors watch over you.
You beat our champion once, but do you think you can do it again?nnCome, take the challenge again! Show us it was not fool's luck.

So now you know my dark secret. It must be horrifyingI haven't been able to bring myself to go down there since this began. I just gave Fakimal a key .nnDo you understand though? Do you realize why this is necessary?
I see her now! And that Daedra has her in its grasp! We must save her!
You are welcome to visit if you keep quiet and be respectful. nnPlease do not disturb the eggs.
Speak with <<1>> in the town square. Perhaps she can point you in the right direction.nnPlease hurry! If we don't discover what's become of Casnar soon, I fear there will be bloodshed.
The pirates have defiled our sacred Hist. They also plague our resting places at the Sunscale Strand to the south.

The Chainwardens tell us to work with the Worm Cult. That they are our friends.nnSome of my friends were Kothringi. I've seen Kothringi in that pit they use to store their zombies.nnThe Worm Cult will never be my friend.
The Saxhleel should control their own lands. Any who stand in our way must be swept aside.nnFortunately, most foreigners can be bribed to step aside with enough money.
There are many troubles in Stormhaven these days. I fear I am not fit to carry a burden as important as that book.
<<1>>! I could not wait any longer. I think the necromancers may suspect the skull no longer lies within the ruins.nnIs... is the spirit friendly? Has it spoken to you?
I feel the power flowing through the ruins once again. You have done well.
Zud-Reen still breathes? His will is truly a thing to behold.nnMay the Hist watch his steps in that treacherous place.
You have to hurry! I think I hear The Thane coming, now!
I understand you and the Abbot pulled quite a trick on Lord Corbolo. nnI told you Villium was a clever man!
Wings of the Moth! The old man was right again. nnYou're his friend, aren't you? You're the one the Prophet spoke of?
<The stone on this tablet has been cracked in half, leaving a chunk of readable script remaining.>
You've robbed these people of their second chance. We had built something great here and you've ruined it.
Is that the crystal? What's happened to it?
What were those loud fiery noises coming from outside?nnWait... I don't want to know.
My guards should have the suspects ready for interrogation and their belongings ready for search. You may proceed when you are ready.

I can rest a little easier now that you have placed the distraction urns at the Imperial Scout camp.nnI will head in that direction soon and observe the effects the urns are having on the scouts. It should be marvelous to watch their confused faces!
The guards refuse to help us!
Go ahead, confiscate the cache. It won't stop the bigger problem.
It looks like this is the end. Thank you for trying to help me.
This book will show us the way - show us what became of the Maruhkites' stolen staff.
The Huntress must know that the end is near. I can feel my own time in this world drawing to a close.

Search the area and see if you can find anything that'll tell us what Mahnor has revealed.nnWe have to be quick. If we don't find out what's been leaked soon, the Imperials will be on Vulkwasten before we know it.
Everything is starting to unravel for The Huntress. I imagine she must be starting to get desperate.nnYou deserve much of the credit for that, <<1>>!
With the Altars destroyed The Huntress won't be able to replinish her army, at least not any time soon.
That's at least a few less Risen that will keep us away from The Huntress.nnI won't be long now until this is all over. Thank you for your help today, <<1>>.
You failed to destroy the book, and are putting it in the hands of intruders?nnI cannot abide this betrayal. Get out of my sight!
I must be sure to look my best before I present this to Layliana. nnOh, what will I say to her? Ugh, I never thought it'd be this unnerving.
Great work! Now we have jewels for the ransom and puffball caps for the sleep potion.nnIt's time to execute my plan. They'll never release Miranda alive unless we have leverage on them.

With the Atronach Binding Tome, we will be able to banish the atronachs the Imperials have summoned or wield them against their masters. It should turn the tide of this fight and rout the Imperial forces once and for all!
The Skull is gone from my hands. It is now up to the Ayleid to guard it. I hope they seal this tomb away, never to be opened again.
I'm back with reinforcements, but I was too late to save the commander, Daedra take it.nnBefore he died, he said he'd sent you on a mission. I hope you succeeded.
Your arrival is well-timed. Our order has been attacked, and I'm at a loss for what to do.
You've returned.nnHas the elixir been given?
The fortress is ours, <<1>>! I knew you could do it!
I can't thank you enough for what you've done for us. nnMainly because now I have to start cleaning up the mess.

Aww, look at how cute those two are.nnThere are many things in this world that are dark and vile, especially in these times. Sometimes the love of another is all we need to pull on through.nnDon't you agree?
Have you come to hear a story?
Take heart. If the staff can be fixed, we'll find a way.nnAs for you, there's something you'll want to pick up before leaving the city.
I could smell something burning. It was not a pleasant smell have you been successful?
The armory is near the center of the fortress grounds. I will stay close to you.
To think that Serge's plan almost worked. Without you  I won't forget what you've done.
Lady Miranda's in the manor house, probably upstairs. Give her the antidote before it's too late!

Things are coming back to me in bits and pieces. The helplessness I felt as my village died... and my guilt at surviving. But there is something I'm forgetting. A duty I was given. nnI need your help one last time, <<1>>.
I don't care what he thinks is right. nnThere must be another way to get that Daedra out of him.
We're under attack!
Pleaseget me out of this! I can pay you, I swear!
I saw Baron Sorick's men taking eggs back to the pools. nnThank Mara! I hope that's the end of it.
Give my regards to the trees outside the ruins, if you would be so kind. Tell them soon we will regain this place.

Is there a reason you're speaking with me?nnI have many customers of great importance. I stock fine art from far and wide. Many have even made the perilous journey from the Alik'r Desert!nnRare goods, indeed ... too rare for your blood. Move along.
There are piles and piles of Imperial garbage to the south and running west along the rivers. You shouldn't have any trouble finding places to search.
You will find the Worm Cultists to the west. Kill them and free the spririts of my people.
I think the presence of so many undead here proves they have no sense of smell.nnOr maybe they do, and didn't want to smell their own brains rotting in the sun anymore.
It looks like you've got some good tricks, <<1>>. nnYou have my respect.
I'm not always sure what the old man is talking about, but in the end he seems to know what to do.nnWhy don't you talk to him now? I think he's on to something.
You must perform the ritual at the shrine on the Castoff Height. It lies to the southwest, between the waterfalls.
I'm looking forward to the day Count Hosni sets us loose on those cultists.nnWe'll make quick work of them.
Did you see his face? I fear the cultist awoke and  suffered. nnWell. It is over. Now for the Daedra.
<<1>>! I could not wait any longer. I think the necromancers may suspect the skull no longer lies within the ruins.nnIs... is the spirit friendly? Has it spoken to you?
You are no longer blinded by her influence, but Rajeren still sees dark clouds hanging around you.
Take some advice from someone who's been here a while. No matter how good it smells, don't eat it.
If you decide to go after the Grinder, just don't let him get the drop on you.nnThat would be the last mistake you'd ever make. Good luck out there.
What a day.
You convinced all three coterie leaders? I am... surprised.nnYou must speak with <<1>>. He is in the shrine to the west, keeping watch over the giant's skull.nnI hope he doesn't do anything rash.
I don't suppose you could move this pile of heads? No?

Compared to what the Ayleids contend with, even in death, the struggle over Hissmir's leadership does seem like the squabble of children.nnThere are things beyond us. I now perceive that current in the waters. It would be best to return the skull.
Divines willing, you'll discover the person responsible for these murders.nnI wish you luck.
There are many wisdoms under the sky, outsider. If you respect ours, we will respect yours.
Go, speak to <<1>>. You've passed her test.
I don't think you wanted to talk to me.
Dividing what we found at Zuuk will take much work. How long will it take you to reach a decision?
I'm relieved you were able to help the Vannes. I'll be heading back to Pariah Abbey now.nnYou should stop by some time. I'll tell you everything you ever wanted to know about the Spirit Wardens.
There's a friendly face. After being surrounded by Supernal Dreamers for so long, it's refreshing.nnThe more I get to know these people, the more I despise them.
So the tales we've heard about that "Worm Cult" - they're true?
<<1>> is one of my most trusted Risen, and his responsibility from here is directing the assault on the Temple. He will know where best you might aid us.
The other Risen will see your handiwork. They will go in after you and ensure the captured spies cannot escape.

Thank you. I was beginning to lose faith. So many selfish people just walk by, abandoning me and my sister to fate.nnIf you can just convince her to leave the house, then she and I can get out of here and go back to Camlorn.
Do you understand the forces with which you meddle, Unbeliever?
Well, at least you're still alive. nnDid you manage to find any evidence that will help exonerate Hosni?
What do you want?
Hmm. You know, the sword doesn't feel especially magical. nnNonetheless, this is what I was sent here to reclaim, and you have aided me in this cause. The Mages Guild thanks you.
Sadly, the lure must be spread close to where you want crocodiles to come. Stormclouds darken this swollen river, threatening all with winds and lightning.nnUntil this is solved, I will not leave.
Thank you for helping the Sergeant get Glasha back. You should talk to him, he's got a reward for you.

The lines on my face tell a sad story: the tale of a woman whose youth was stolen by circumstance.nnI was widowed even before I flowered. I did what I thought was right. I assumed the burden of leadership, but I paid for that choice. I paid dearly.
Now the trainees complain when I demonstrate thrusts to the head. Can't please anyone now a days.
You killed Galthis's minions? We mustn't get our hopes up, though. Not until Galthis himself is dead.

Did you pass through Crestshade by any chance? Do you know what's happening there?nnMy wife, the mayor of Crestshade, made me lead this group away when the fiends attacked. I keep hoping she'll walk into camp any moment now.
Why are you still here? I can't keep Ashton from her soul gems forever. nnIf you want futher training go to Wayrest. The runecrafters there are said to be sane.
The Covenant thanks you for joining the war effort! With talented crafters like yourself at our back, there's no challenge we can't overcome. nnAkatosh bless your wares, friend.
Go away! So far, all the crazy people and monsters have just ignored this house. If you keep knocking they'll come and kill you!nnAnd then they'll break down the door and kill me!
Just now, I heard a sound, as though the forest around this place sighed with joy and relief. Tell me what has happened, <<1>>.
It is good that you come, <<1>>. Someone has to join Drahir in the killing.
Good job with the salvage work on the dead Imperials. It's the filthy part of war no one ever talks about.
I suppose I should be happy if the countess has finally chosen a husband,nnPerhaps it's time for me to move on.
Look for the Lion Guard scout on the road to Steelheart Moorings.nnHe seemed eager for a fight. I'm worried he may have taken on more than he can handle.
Perhaps our reunion can bring peace to this place. I sense that something has changed.
Slowly, by divine grace, my powers return. nnSoon I shall once again be ready to contend with Molag Bal's monstrosities.
Where's <<1>>? Did you find him?
I'm glad you're back. Your presence seems to distract the Daedra quite intensely. Maybe now I can determine where my summoning ritual went awry.

Damned foreigners. We've had nothing but trouble ever since the duke married King Fahara'jad's daughter.nnAnd now they bring an army to our doorstep and expect the Knights of the Flame to just stand aside?
How goes the search? Have you discovered anything yet?
Giddy will feast for a moon's turn. Praise <<1>>!
If you die in this endeavor, we will not weep. Not for an outsider.nnSucceed, though, and my tribe will welcome you as clanfriend.
I can't believe my suspicions were so far from the truth. The assassin being a Breton only makes this situation more volatile.nnPlease, tell Sir Hughes and ask him to resolve this matter swiftly.
I wouldn't go up there, if I were you.nnThe entire farm's been burned down. Scamps are everywhere, and Mister Nurin, he's gone missing!
I never imagined that getting locked in the stocks could be this painful.nnI hope you haven't forgotten about me.
I spoke to Sal, but I couldn't reason with him.nnHe refuses to let Dabienne go until <<1>> is back in Koeglin Village, safe and sound.
It's about time. I assume the duke sent you? I am his personal messenger, you know.nnWell, what are you waiting for? Untie me!
As I said, I appreciate your help before, but in this situation, I can't afford to have someone questioning my authority.nnPlease. Just leave town. Easier for all of us.
Haha! My spirit soars to see you return in one piece. And you found the ledger, Ruptga bless you.nnPlease, take it to this constable and prove that we are friends and in need of assistance.
If you can just take care of those portals, I'm sure the rest of the scamps will wander off eventually.
Turns out that almost everyone in town thinks Pascal has been acting strangeeven the guards.nnDid you find anything that explains his behavior?
If you find Lucas, I'll be eternally grateful. He's just an innocent boy.nnIn a minute, I'll have to go get dinner ready, but I'm going to keep his plate warm.
My mother may have gone totally insane, but it's all right. My dad's here, and we're still a family.

Gods strike you! Couldn't you have just waited five more minutes?nnThe slavers outside the tent were talking about where their base of operations is  then they got interrupted. I'm guessing they saw you.nnMy mom sent you, didn't she?
I don't understand. Sir Hughes served me for so many years. Loyally. Faithfully. nnWhy would he murder my wife?
Don't let anyone fool you. Any conscript who's unhappy with his life here can skulk off at any time.nnThe conscripts stay here for a reason. They want to fight ogres.
Lucas. Lucas. Lucas. That's all she talks about. nnMargot's worried sick about the boy. At this point, you'd think she'd have gotten over it.
Well, that didn't work. Time to come up with a new plan  again.
You are either suicidal or simply very stupid to barge in here without my permission. I will waste no further time with you. Be gone!
I didn't know his wife was here, too.nnWhen he dies, who will care for their children?
Listen to this braggart. Claims he could drop us all with a hand behind his back. The nerve.nnAnd King Fahara'jad claims these warriors are here in a diplomatic capacity? Preposterous!
I was useless. The last thing I remember clearly is kissing Rosa before going to sleep.nnMy poor Rosa.
I don't know who's been keeping the Ebonheart Pact busy, but I've seen more of the beach than I have in days.
I feel there are still others who need help.nnSeek out <<1>> near the town square. Find what disturbs him and help free him from his worries.
You know what I'd love to do? I'd love to lay waste to every last one of these poxy clowns, but the constable says we're to just guard the door.nnAt least I'll get to watch them starve.
Soon, my husband and I will travel to Wayrest to get away from these gossipy provincial villagers.
Twenty Blackhearts dead! Squawk!
The Herd Mother blesses us with these challenges, <<1>>.nnHow else can we learn about the lives our ancestors lived?
When we've chased off the last of these sabre cats, our lands will be safe, and our horses will roam freely again.
Well done, <<1>>!

It is the legend of <<1>> that he cannot die within his stronghold, this <<2>>. My father proved it true.nnHis crew speaks of this legend, and of the spirits their captain keeps in thrall. Stop the source of his magic, and Blackheart will be undone.
You spoke with General Thoda? Please tell us, tell the Duchess what he said.
I will return home and speak with King Fahara'jhad. I hope we can now focus on the loss of the one we loved rather than the crime that took her life. nnTime heals all wounds, or so they say.

Nothing about this has been easy, and it will be hard to look back on these events with anything other than sadness.nnI am glad you came along, though. Without you, we might not be able to look back on these days at all.
I've heard not everyone in the Union likes Count Hosni's new direction. Maybe, if you ask, someone in there will help you.
I can breathe again, knowing we're all safe at last. nnBut you, my friend. Now we have you to worry about.
Have you changed your mind? My offer still stands.
Trouble and trouble has come to Fell's Run. I hope you aren't bringing more, stranger.

What brings you to the end of the world? You're a new face, not from one of the Shornhelm houses, by the looks of you.nnPardon my mood. News that he's using the Lightless Remnants up there makes a positive outcome rather unlikely.

Verandis be damned! I will not stand by as our own soldiers are used against us.nnThis is why Verandis ordered us away from the spire. He knew we would be easy pickings if we simply charged in. This is maddening!
Move along. The general is not entertaining guests right now.
<<1>> is the only champion left.nnWatch it: he's not called the Scourge of the Arena for nothing.
I'm glad to be safe and sound by the fire. I don't think I'll be travelling the mountain passes alone again for some time.
Good luck against those champions!
My blood fever poultice could do a lot of good right now. I hope you can find enough spider ichor.nnOh, look! There goes a spider now!
We will need armor to fight these monsters: armor and luck.nnI hope the Nords don't invade while we're under attack here.
I knew that the ancients must have sent you to us, <<1>>.nnMay their spirits watch over you.
I can hardly believe it. <<1>> killed, and here I am speaking to the one who did it.nnI hated that Orc. If I could watch him die again, I would.
Revenge is sweet.nnIf only it could have been me out there. I'd have torn that beast's legs off one at a time.
The Midnight Union's lackeys are all over Hammerdeath Arena.nnThe death of my brothers will be answered in blood!
We surely would have perished in that cave if not for your heroics, <<1>>. Thank you.
Your friends in the Daggerfall Covenant would gladly send you to Balfiera Island. They always need more reinforcements for their war. Just ask for a battlemaster in one of your alliance cities.
The Zero Stone will restore the staff. It was laid by the gods themselves, back before the dawn.nnIt's so simple! And yet  I fear the journey will be anything but.
My father went to greet the returning foals. You'll find him down at the paddock.

Before you can reach Shiri, you'll have to unseal the vault. You must destroy <<1>> and <<2>>. Then collect blood from their undead husks.nnYou'll also find one of the Ansei Wards on the corpse of <<2>>. Perhaps you can save it from its fate.
You're back. What happened?
I've trained some of Northpoint's finest soldiers.nnThese farmers will be a challenge, but at least they're no strangers to hard work.
You did well. Roy couldn't have handled things any better.
Welcome back! Do you need more flowers?
Welcome to my shop. How may I help you?
Please hurry, <<1>>.nnI might not have much time left.
It is finished. Alik'r is saved!
Alik'r is in your debt. Thank you!
Your brave actions  saved Alik'r. Thank you!
Have you and Grenna found out anything new?
Save the villagers first, then we can talk.
Good luck in your travels. I expect to hear more great things of you in the very near future.
Not more pig trouble, I hope.
Please don't let Glutton become bacon. He's much too young to be eaten.
They were hiding here among us, weren't they? I thought as much. nnI hate missing out on killing werewolves, but I had, well, something else I had to keep an eye on.
I'm getting too old for this. Wasn't fast enough to avoid that blade to my knee.
The Red Rooks are done here. We'll be able to clear the rest of them out.
Traveler, there's trouble ahead. Bandits. You should turn back. We can't guarantee your safety.
Who goes there? Identify yourself.

Get everyone back here and we can keep them safe. For a while. In the meantime, we'll work on what to do next.nnAnd make sure you put those fires out. This building won't provide much protection if it burns to the ground.
Faolchu's hairy  Of all things!
I understand that saving my husband was just the latest in a series of heroic acts to save Stormhaven.nnThis was a threat to the Daggerfall Covenant as a whole, so Alik'r thanks you as well.
I don't want to die! I don't want to die!
Please, don't get too far ahead. I don't want to be left behind.
I should have never left her. I ... I don't know what I'll do from here.nnHer face ... I'll never forget her face.
Thanks again for helping out with our training program.
I should have never left her. I ... I don't know what I'll do from here.nnHer face ... I'll never forget her face.

He killed them, didn't he? By Stendarr, that's one more score we need to settle with Faolchu. nnIt's my fault. I should have acted sooner. I shouldn't have waited for proof that the Duke had been cursed.
Haven't seen that Fausta woman around have you? Oh, never mind. I'll find her later.
Please hurry. There's no telling what they plan to do with the captive women.nnThis is all my fault. I wish we'd never left Camlorn.
Alik'r is in your debt. Thank you!
Your brave actions have saved Alik'r. Thank you!
A spirit spoke to you? You need to continue this line of investigation and see where it leads.
Wonder why Lord Diel is so interested in keeping these things alive? What can you learn when a damn harpy is trying to peck your eyes out?
I'll never regret this decision. I will do my best to find happiness with my family, as my father wished.
I'm not sure I completely understand what's going on here. There is a harpy menaceisn't there?
Quick! Hide the eggs in his bed before he gets back to his tent!
Taking a bit of reward, eh? Go ahead. I'll be taking some to pay the others, myself.
You found Guy. I hope you can save the others, too.
Your actions have changed the balance of power in the bog.nnMother Murk's power wanes. Now the bog belongs to the Wyrd.
You've lifted a great burden from my heart, friend.
Those wizards called our ancestors from the necropolis! Why did they do that? What did we do to deserve this?
You made it here at last, <<1>>, as was foreseen. I'm glad I was here to meet you. nnYou are the key to defeating the Withered Hand. To do so completely, you must defeat them in Satakalaam.

I have many friends still lying in the stables. Killing the Daedra and harvesting their hearts would help the at-Aswals.nnThen make your way to the tower north of <<1>> and speak to the stablemaster. Once the beasts are gone, we can bury the dead.
That is the Gem of Westtry's Torment. How you acquired it, I don't want to know.  nnBut quickly, use it to free the villagers from this terrible curse.
Hawthorn shrubs grow throughout the village. Just pluck a few berries and get them to Muriel at the apothecary shop.
Don't worry about me, Captain. You've got a town to defend. I'll tend to any wounded who find their way here.
Captain Rosalind? I'm sorry. I couldn't hold them off.
Now that the Daedra have been thinned out, we should be able to contain them. Thank you!
<This corpse was stabbed and slashed beyond recognition.>
Thanks to your courage, I can return to caring for the sacred waters here.nnI will be forever grateful.
By the scrolls, we are fortunate to have found an ally in you, <<1>>. I pray you find <<2>> safe and sound.
Well, we're still alive.nnBut it's only a matter of time, of course. Even if we escape the hags, there's still the werewolves.
Aha! Perfect! Say though, you didn't happen to pick up a few giant's toes while you were at the bazaar, did you?
This should be interesting.
Best of luck, my brave friend.
Knock those hags' heads together!
Great job! The Daedric portal is finally closed!nnWe are in your debt, <<1>>.
It seems we've created a ripple in time itself. nnSomeone needs to go and find out what our spell actually accomplished.
Go, find Alana. We'll deal with Faolchu, once and for all.
Parmion will want to see these orders immediately. nnHe's in our camp to the east, in case you forgot that as well.
For a second, I thought I heard <<1>>. I must be losing my mind.
Soon <<1>> will leave this dangerous Lanylantown and go somewhere nice.nnShe heard of a place called Saakatalama? Maybe <<1>> will sell something there.
My brethren will hear of your actions. You have proven yourself a true ally of the Ancestor Moths.
My sisters return to camp. Speak with the guardian.
I shall return the rest of the <<1>> to the King of Daggerfall.nnBy rights, the treasure is his, but it doesn't hurt to gain the favor for the Ancestor Moths.
A tiny blow has been struck against our tormenter.
You return. My brother and sister monarchs await word of your success.
The tower in the north courtyard contains the gate works. Get in there and lock it down. nnIf you stop more werewolves from coming in, we should be able to deal with the ones that are already here.
My spirit knows peace again. Thank you, <<1>>.
You return? I cannot believe  do you have the relics?
What a fantastic plan, I must say! So much excitement!
That was terrifying! A tad thrilling, too. But terrifying!
Stendarr bless you.
Thanks for helping the Duke. I'm glad I don't have to have his death on my conscience.
Take the path down to the beach. nnI'm too weak to walk, so I'll use my magic and meet you there.
General Gautier's troops are to the east, in the siege camp. nnThe wolves are on the offensive, so watch yourself.
Let Gautier know we're safe. I've got to get the wounded to the healers.
Thank you for directing the women here. They will be well cared for.
On your way, forester apprentice. Next step is journeyman. Learn more recipes. Craft more gear.nnGot some for sale, if you want. Luck in the trees.
Who are you? Are you working for the Withered Hand, or are you one of those Imperial dogs?
Go. We have nothing more to say.
Who  who are you? Please don't kill me.
I'll protect the portal and keep the Bloodthorn at bay. You go rescue my father.
Did you break the spell? I feel... different.
It seems I misjudged you. Thank you for assisting my warriors.nnWould you speak to Zal at-Zazir? Find out how successful he's been in dealing with the poison.
Now I know who sent you. It was Morwha herself!
We're committed to aiding the Lion Guard, so do as the General suggests.nnIt's not like we have a better option at the moment.

Thank you for helping us, wayfarer. nnI know my father explained everything, but I would add a desperate plea. Please do not just accept Enneh's word. Look elsewhere in the town. Whatever it takes to find Casnar and bring him here.
You know, I think we might actually have a chance of pulling this off.nnWell  if you can actually convince Uncle Thakh to let me out . Hmm. Maybe we don't have a chance after all.
Welcome to Bergama, wayfarer! We have the finest musical instruments in Hammerfell!nnI am just closing up shop now, but if you want a harp, a lute, or even a drum, come back another time.
Try your hand at my gaming tables.  We've got cards, dice, and good company. nnStay as long as you want. You might win big. No guarantees, of course.
My man will let you pass now.
And here we are, at the inn, all safe and sound. More or less. nnWe saw the light and followed you inside.
You placed my stone well. I should be protected this close to the tree.

The Eight protect you, stranger. The Sentinel Guard is looking for assistance, and you look like a capable sort.nnNormally, I'd never ask someone just arrived to Sentinel for this kind of aid, but an outlander is exactly what we need right now.
So spiders flooded the mine!nnI hope everyone got out all right.
Please speak to me once you have finished your business here with <<1>>.nnI know she's been awaiting your return.
Bahir's brief capture doesn't seem to have phased him. Thank you for your help today, <<1>>.
Once Bahir reappeared, the dockworkers finally began to calm down. I think we have almost everything under control here. Sure, they're still a bit wary, but who wouldn't be?

Finally! Someone who's not afraid to do the dirty work. Someone to clean up my docks! I watched you from the window until I heard those necromancers downstairs. nnBut I thought Maujad was coming here toodid you see him?
We just watched boats filled with Bloodthorn cultists sail away from the docks. What happened down there?
Your advances are sweet, walker. nnMaybe we will cross paths again in the next life and things will be different.

Thank you for your help, <<1>>. I'll return to Bergama once my horse has rested from the long run.nnAnd don't worry. I'll send someone to fetch Sergeant Ra'ud's body and consecrate it before the Withered Hand can raise him from the dead.
Darien talks of nothing but wine and women, but behind his bluster he's a better tactician than his father. nnThough that's not saying much.
Will someone just let me know whether or not we're going to get paid for this? I could really use the gold.
That didn't seem right.
Thank you again for collapsing the tunnel. Now all we need to do is chase off the Imperial dogs that are still here.nnTo think this scum would ally with corrupted madmen from the Withered Hand!
I have prepared a new body for <<1>>. He will be a terror on the battlefield!nnDo you have the souls we need to complete the ritual?
You walk toward me with such purpose ... is there something on your mind, my dear?

I'm sure that you realize that with the Reachmen bearing down on us, I have a great many matters to attend to.nnI absolutely do not wish to be rude, but I must be going. Come back another time and I will endeavor to answer all your questions.
Good day to you. Have you come at the summons of her ladyship?
Ah, you're back. And in a timely manner. Did you find the crown?
Grave wort is very common in <<1>>.nnThe plants have a distinctive musty odor and pale, fragile flowers. You'll need one plant for each tomb.
The owner must be in the Mages Guild.nnWhy they would take this poor boy's body, I don't know. You must find out before harm comes to him.
May Tu'whacca bless this place at last.
Who are you? What business do you have bothering a dead man?
I trust General Gautier. Follow his orders and the city will be ours again.
Get into that tower and lock that gate. We'll be right behind you.
Please, do not let me linger.nnComplete the ritual and remove the curse.
I wouldn't stick around here. Reinforcements are on the way. They'll take over now.
Necromancy? Why, I never would have dreamed .nnIf the Reach magicians have infiltrated our ranks so easily, our mages must be on alert. I will let them know.
Go and find that bothersome noble. She's not far, just down the passageway.
You showed great bravery entering the mines, <<1>>. The stories about you are true.
With the heirs of Suturah running loose in Alik'r, the Aldmeri Dominion is the last problem we need to worry about.nnThanks to you, they won't be coming back.

Don't worry. I'll take the priest to Prince Adrien. nnHopefully, the prince has regained enough strength to walk to the church. I don't think I can carry him in full plate, and I'm betting our friendly priest here won't be much help.
The Ash'abah need your help. Go to the Tears of the Dishonored to the east.nnI pray that my vision did not come too late.
What the Prince has become ... it's an insult to the Divines!
Whatever that thing is, it is no longer my grandson.nnIt must be destroyed!
Please, don't hurt me! I don't want to die!nnWait, you're not the creature that attacked my father. You're not even one of the Montclairs.
Though I hate the undead, I can't help but pity the men and women they once were. nnTu'whacca, guide me!
No! No, please! Leave me alone! I haven't done anything.
You've done my family a great service today.nnWe won't forget what you've done for us.
I don't remember inviting you aboard. Make your business quick, or you'll be picking seaweed out of your teeth.

The captain headed in the direction of the inn. You should be able to catch up. Find out what she's up to and then take all this to the queen.nnIf this prompts her into action, it might just be worth it. She would make a wonderful ruler, you know.
And the troublemaker appears again!nnTake care you know your place. The next time we meet, my greeting may not be so cordial.

Why would she ask to meet me in the gardens behind the castle? I'd prefer a less uncouth area, one with fewer flies and peasants.nnI'm sure she has her reasons, but I'm too busy with my negotiations anyway.

This will take time, but the gargoyles will eventually return to normal. You've taken away a potentially deadly resource from the Imperials.nnAnd you've shown that I can trust some people. That change is more difficult and will also take time.
You certainly made short work of those Elves. There seem to be few odd skeletons down here, no problem for you, I'm sure.nnNow, I assume you found the old tome in my camp?
The stone rules the flesh, here as everywhere. Flesh must always yield to stone.
You are a noble spirit and a brave soul, my friend. nnYou've done me a good turn here, and by exposing Stibbons' uselessness, you've done Lady Laurent a favor too.

You're not one of Gharzu's men! I thought  I mean, I wasn't trying to do anything! It was just for the gold. I's rough nowadays!nnThey meet us in the South Ward, where they pay us. Strange coins, but gold is gold!
Have you crafted the ring?
Evoker Valinwe can be found in Aldcroft, to the east of here.
There is an ill feeling surrounding that ship.nnI will pray for your success.
Have you crafted the ring
It's good to see the Duke back in Camlorn. This is where he belongs.
Get the recipe from Falbert. Once you learned it talk to me
The crafting table is outside. People complained aobut the smell inside.
He wandered as a vulture circles its prey. But he truly has no sense of direction, and thus managed to wander farther away with each passing moment.nnWe must find him.
A familiar scent surrounds you. Did the Sentinel send you? What do you hold?

That certainly wasn't my finest hour, but I thought  I thought it was Arkay. I thought he was giving me a second chance.nnThere's nothing more foul than this creature's deception. It must've hailed from the depths of Oblivion itself!

I've known Stenwick since I was a child. Just because we didn't agree on many things, doesn't mean his burial tradition should be ignored.nnI'd hoped for a change with his death, but it seems the princess will continue the Sentinel's work. A shame.

The <<1>> should make itself known to you. You'll have to keep your eyes open for a sign.nnOf course, there's other, less subtle ways of getting its attention. They say the forest feels the death of every creature.
Where are the rest of the reinforcements? Are you all they sent?
You're not from the Reach, are you? Sometimes, it's hard to tell.
<Medya's torso is covered in old and faded Reachman tattoos which were previously obscured by her humble peasant's attire.>
I can't believe it. You gave the tools to Tamien? How could you?nnNow I'll never get back to Lady Laurent's good graces!
Stenwick only asked for Wyrd's blessing to be kind, but they don't seem ready to help him, do they?
This beautiful woman from the Mages Guild just arrived. Says she knows you! You can introduce me later.nnI was right about the amulets, though, wasn't I?
Lead on, <<1>>! I'm a gardener, not a fighter.nnThe sooner we get away from these angry spirits, the better.
The rescued miners are singing your praises. Well done!
The king will be grateful for what we've done here. Some of Angof's minions are still running loose, but it's nothing we can't handle.nnMaybe things will finally return to normal now.
All Crosswych is talking about you. nnThe Red Rooks are on the run. If they try to stop, we'll chase them right out of town.
Thanks to you, I have <<1>> back!nnI won't forget what you've done for us.
What answers the call is the Hunger.
Get to Lainlyn, comrade. <<1>> will fill you in on the details when you get there.
Report! nnHave you stopped the Withered Hand from recruiting the Saltwalker Company?
That amulet reminds me of happier times. The sunlight on her hair. The way she laughed. Her smile .nnShe meant the world to me. Getting this amulet back brings me hope, <<1>>.
My aching back! And just look what all this laundry is doing to my hands!nnStill, if this is the only way I can earn ration tickets, then I'll do laundry day and night until we can return home.
Well, we've been through quite a bit together, haven't we? nnI think I like you. You're fun! Stop by and visit if you're ever in the neighborhood!
I have a strange sense of liberation now, with my thirst for revenge quenched, and my material ties dissolved. I could go anywhere  be anything .
You'll find the dead throughout the ruins.nnPlenty remained after the Ra Gada.
Congratulations. You did what I could not, <<1>>.
