Hm. I suppose that answers the question. Our fates are no more fixed than the wind that blows across these dunes.nnUnless  do you think maybe that was not the right wind storm? Do you believe that maybe there is another  just about to appear?

I'm sorry I wasn't there when you killed Angof. I needed to get the others back here safety. I think they'll recover. Now if only Darien would stop distracting me with his chatter.nnAnyway, you really are something.
I'll speak to the matriarch. She may offer us aid.nnThe bloodletting I leave to you.
Given how many of us were hurt at the garrison, prisoners aren't high on the priority list.nnI hope we can get his wounds treated quickly.
Good luck. Show no mercy to these elven invaders!
Always remember the lesson you've learned here today, friend. Fate does not control those who are willing to step to the fore. Set your hand against fortune, and you will see your wishes fulfilled.
Medya needed to die for all that she's done here.nnThe people of Evermore need not hear whatever lies she would use to defend herself at a trial.

Clarisse is lucky I'm sharing this information with her. I'm just smart enough to know she probably won't be the one reassembling the amulet. nnI can't allow the curse to befall someone just doing her bidding.
Now I must pray that the gargoyles return to sleep before any more damage is done.
So <<1>> is finally gone for good.nnYou have no idea how much that eases my mind, <<2>>.
I heard what you did. Congratulations! <<1>> won't threaten <<2>> again, that's for certain!
We must hurry, before Kerbol does anything more to hurt my husband!

He speaks the truth. I've bound everyone here to this village, but by doing so, freed them from the curse of lycanthropy. They all chose it willingly.nnThink what you want of it, but each of our sacrifices is for the greater good.
My commander will hear of your exploits, I promise you.

My father believes it's time for us to integrate with the humans. I trust him, but I can't help but feel a bit frightened.nnOur kind hasn't always been able to ignore our base impulses. People have a good reason not to trust us.
Is that  is that blood all mine? All of it? I don't think that's good.nnIf I die, I swear by Malacath that I'll come back for you.
You have shown great skill in your hunt. Lord Hircine will be pleased.
Now that you've picked a lizard, you can enter it in a race. Put your lizard in a starting cage when you're ready, and let's watch that baby fly!
Welcome. I've heard we've you to thank for ridding <<1>> of those Imperials.nnI'm glad to see you're paying us a visit.
I'm certainly glad you came to Crosswych. People wanted to fight back, but they just needed some encouragement.
You have a triumphant look about you. Spit it out, have you the key or not?
<The dog pants happily.>
If you plan to enter your lizard in a race, you'll need to put it in a starting cage.
<<1>> will never again threaten <<2>>, thanks to you.
I wish you luck in consecrating those foul bones.nnNo necromancer should be suffered to live, let alone find undeath.
The trolls weren't much of a nuisance, at least to anyone outside of the woods, but lately, they've been getting bolder  and hungrier.nnIt's a shame that it's come to this.
Food will be harder to come by now that we aren't getting help from the Imperials. I hope that we will still be able to feed everyone.
Excellent work, <<1>>!nnThe souls of Motalion Necropolis rest easily once again.
I'm glad most of my people took the cure. Whatever benefits being a werewolf may bring, living apart from society seems too high a price.
Bonebreaker's crypt is northeast of this chapel, beneath the hillside.nnThe entrance is near the shore of Halcyon Lake.
It hurts  it hurts! Go  away!

In addition to the public praise, I must add my own private words of appreciation, wayfarer.nnYou not only saved the kingdom, you also saved its king. My reign would have been buried in the sands had you not intervened. Thank you.
<<1>> told us what you need.nnI'm  afraid  of going through that.

They don't suspect, do they? Surprise! Surprise on the dancers. Surprise on Madame Lurue. nnHer black book is in her sanctuary, beyond the dancers. Stop them all! End of the dance. It's time to go home.
I think my luck's about to change for the better  oh yes.
I'll be sure to report your bravery to my superiors, friend.
Now that we've completed the repairs, we need more laborers to work the rain catchers, or we'll fall behind Sentinel's demands for water.
Mara's mercy! You scared the life out of me!
She succeeded with your help.nnMind you, that is nothing against the princess. Gurles needed help, too.
Destroy the relics! They keep me trapped here.
No one died today. It's all because of your help.nnMay Tava lend speed your steps, traveler.
Your actions today have saved lives, wayfarer. You should be proud.nnRemember that as you bed down tonight.
We will scout the Imperial forces while you free the others from the barracks.
Now that you have the goods, take them to Ildani, and then to the buyers. nnDon't worry. We'll be watching. If anything goes wrong, we'll have your back.
My son is safe and my family has been restored to me.nnYou are truly a gift from merciful Stendarr.
Without your help, I would have been a meal for the jackals.
Once the commander is dead, the rest of the Imperial troops will scatter.
I hardly see why you deserved payment at all. Still, you are one of the few who actually bothered to return to let me know.
I'm glad we won't be seeing any overgrown alligators in these parts anytime soon.
<The captain lies writhing on the ground. Nightmare fire streams from braziers to his struggling form.>
Speak to Lorelia and listen to her wisdom.
This is the entrance to her lair. I'm sure of it. nnI don't see her in there, so I think it's safe to go in and search for the stolen relics.
Go away before the guards catch us!
I look forward to doing business with you in the future!
Thanks to the Baandari, I can maintain a pretty decent lifestyle.
You know, we're supposed to be keeping this relationship subtle.
Have you gotten all those focus pieces yet?
I must insist that you go away, leave me be, and do whatever it is you intend to do with whomever else you intend to do it.
Hurry! You need to switch the orders before they start to move out for Volenfell. nnThey could strike camp suddenly. You never know with armies  it's always hurry up and wait.
I'd check the Mages Guild in Daggerfall if I were you. They must have a scroll or a tome that will tell us how to speak with the spirits of the dead.

I wish we'd be rid of Alimah's Gallants. The idiots don't wear armor, and they're constantly running around where the enemy isn't. Cowards.nnAnd don't get me started on the stench of horse droppings. Confound those horses! They drive me to drink.
Praise the Golden Eye! That foul creature could be here any moment, and I wouldn't have wanted to face her without you.nnWhatever happens, we can't let her get to the shrine! Are you ready?
Do you dare to ask more of me?
We should hurry. The longer the connection to Cold Harbor remains open, the more danger we're in.nnWe need to break that connection as soon as possible.
Who's there?nnI'm afraid I'm not long for this world.
The Imperials captured us on our way to the old tower to see my father. We would all have surely perished if not for your help.nnSomeday, I hope to repay your kindness.
Our captive convinced you to help him, didn't he? nnHe's sending you into a trap, mark my words.
Quickly! There isn't much time!

Look for the Bloodthorn envoy in the central part of the ruins.nnBe careful though. Once he falls, disguise or not, they'll come after you with everything they have. Only your wits and your weapons will get you out of there in one piece.
Now we have to extinguish the signal fires.
We'll make sure the Dominion are stopped here.
We'll forever be in your debt. nnIf you are heading north, I do have one last favor to ask.
The dead rest easier in their graves. The Barrows, and the brothers Althen, owe you a debt traveler.
The eternal flame is in the chamber to the south.nnIf you can bring its flame to the braziers in this room and succesfully relight them all, you will have my fealty.
Have you dealt with Leonce yet? As long as he lives, we'll never be able to overcome the Fell's Brigade.
You don't look like one of those vampires or bloodfiends, so I guess you're welcome. This is Camp Tamrith. We're sheltering the refugees from Crestshade and the surrounding countryside here.
The fractures were a threat to all of <<1>>  and perhaps all of Tamriel!nnClosing them was an act of true heroism.
Did you escort my brother?
Save Captain Janeve!
Mother is hungry, but it makes me a little sick to watch her eat.nnAre you looking for the Captain? They dragged her into the cave. The Bad One is going to do terrible things to her.
The militia camp? Why, it's just to the north, right outside of town.nnI can't believe Leonce would betray us like this. I hope he doesn't give you too much trouble.
We lost too many good soldiers today. But the four of us survive thanks to you.nnThe rest of the Lion Guard will hear of your exploits today, friend.
And here is the savior of my people, my city, and me! We are all in your debt, friend.
You - you are no goblin! Why does a <<1>> possess the medallion?
I'm glad we won't be seeing any overgrown alligators in these parts anytime soon.

My father's house is northeast of us. You should find a bar of silver within the dresser inside. nnThe silver and the shards of the original medallion should allow our blacksmith to reforge the medallion.
I'm glad I brought more troops with me than usual on this patrol.nnStill, I don't have anyone who can get to those prisoners any time soon.
We're dealing with the harpies as fast as we can, I assure you. Now please, address any specific complaints to one of the guardsmen.

Nuwarrah's family has alway been a thorn in my side. Now that I helped save the city, she'll probably host a feast in honor of the deed.nnThat could mar my reputation with the Thieves Guild. The woman is impossible.
If you head into the caves on the eastern edge of Bangkorai, be careful. The wyresses stay away from those parts whenever possible.nnMay Hircine guide your steps.
State your business, traveler. Fell's Run has enough trouble. We really don't need any more.
Orcs are parasites, sucking the very marrow from our town. They are fur-fleas, getting fat and bloated on the blood of our people. The time has come to end the infestation once and for all!

Did you hear what that son of a troll said about us? It's slander, I tell you! Slander!nnLeonce is just trying to divert attention from his own guilt. If our cowardly constable won't do something about this, we will!

If we don't retake the garrison soon, I'm not sure how we'll hold <<1>> together.nnOnce the Imperials entrench here, they'll be able to strike with impunity from this position. The whole war could be lost, starting here.
Help my father and brother. I'm sure they'll want you to make the effigies as soon as possible.
Deprecated.
Make sure those beasts understand what it means to face the might of my clan!

The Imperials must think we'd never notice they're using the same tactic over and over again. We'll make sure they won't be practicing necromancy much longer.nnPlease hurry to the crypt. It's on the eastern side of the garrison.
All you need do is toss some of the musk on the fire-warmed rocks. The smell will do the rest.nnI'll be moving downwind.
I think it's best if we go our separate ways. Though you helped considerably, I can't take that risk again.
May the gods grant you luck against the Imperials. Many more are on our side that it appears.
Thanks to you, we've finally got this town back under control.
It's not safe to speak so openly. The sand carries whispers wherever it goes.
What are you doing in my home? Did Quatrius send you?nnI've done everything he's asked! I won't suffer any more humiliation at his hands!
You need to kill <<1>>. Then seek the aid of heroes buried within the necropolis.nnYou won't defeat <<2>> without help.

I'll meet you outside the gates of Evermore, past the bazaar near the Mages Guild. Ready yourself, for it will not be as forgiving as this mortal plane.nnThe portal to Cold Harbor must be prepared outside the city walls. We must do this safely.
Our resources at the Mages Guild are not unlimited, but with the word of <<1>> behind you, I'm sure you will be well-received.
We'll keep these folk safe.nnYou put out those fires and put the fear of Northpoint into those cursed Nords!
Baron Chirane's home is by the fountain across from the duchess's manor.
I have no further business with you. Begone!
Thank you again for your assistance, <<1>>.nnAs you know, there's more to securing a city than defending its walls.
Looking for water for the fires? I'd try the farmhouses near Captain Balmont.
Excuse me, I have to ask someone . the others here  they don't always let me speak .nnPlease, help me. I'm not a real soldier, but someone had to step up when the prince fell.
Nasir sells no goods, only information. More dangerous, more profitable.
Thank you again. If it wasn't for you, we would've lost a lot of good people today.
Luck to you. I'll see if we can hold this line in case you return  I mean, until you return.

Grandmaster Tanval says that if the Covenant gets the heart, it could let them raise a Brother of Strife against us. That thing could wipe out Ebonheart.nnWhatever it costs, we've got to keep that weapon out of their hands.
My eggs must twine with the coral, if it's to join us against the Covenant.
Well, get going. The grandmaster needs to act now.
Did you recover the relic?
If you haven't already, report to <<1>>. He's just west of here, interviewing the soldiers.
You have the <<z:1>>?
A living soul? It has been so long. To walk the river again, it is so strange. And so sad.
I don't understand Furon's plan, but you shouldn't keep him and that clever brother of his waiting.
Still no news? Work quickly before his crimes are discovered. I will not let my brother ruin our house!
Are you looking for <<1>>? He's on the far side of town from here.nnLook for the temple.
Varon is very upset with me
The coral child lives, and will protect us from the Daggerfall Covenant. We are once again fruit of the same tree.
The hatchling has been found, unhurt. This is good. nnGirvas speaks like an angry wind. Perhaps you should calm his blustering.
Oh, great. This is all I need.
Traveler you  you found my daughter. In the midst of all this, you found my Morvani.
Use this medicine on the injured. If they complain it is Argonian-made, ignore them.nnWhen you are done, find <<1>>. He is near the center of town.
F'lah, you'll find the flasks of blinding light upstairs. Use them to reveal the assassin infiltrators. Put an end to their plans.
Activate the first four plates in these tunnels and meet me in the last chamber. Go well, and go quietly.
Curse the Morag Tong! Nothing but murderers for hire.nn<<1>> deserved a better end than this.
The assassins creep on the edges of the fort, by the walls. Smash the flasks and kill any assassins you uncover.
We need to get that thing under guard, and fast. Get it to Holgunn back at camp. There's a quick exit to the west. Look for the vines.
You hold the heart, yet the coral lives. Once I saw it was dying, I had no choice but to merge myself with the coral. We are one now: one tree with the same roots.
One day, I will visit the Tribunal Temple in Deshaan.nnI will hear the word of Vivec from his own lips.
Remember, subdue, then use the whistle. If you don't, they'll just start fighting again.nnI'll be at my mine, west of town. I've got to salvage what I can.
Ah, do you have what <<1>> needs? He's in the temple.
When you go for the banners, watch for the guards on the towers.
Yes! That just might work .nnFind the skulls and bring them to Khralek's altar. We may be dead, but we still have power. We can pull Khralek to you.
Captain Hjolm?
Move along, travelerunless you have news about Vartis Dareel.
Watch yourself. Tangling with Orcs is dangerous work.
Do you have enough <<z:1>>?nnSee <<2>> in the temple. He knows what to do with it.
<You've taken the items in this chest.>
I've sent dispatches to locate Scout Fontbonne. I'll let you know when we've found him.
You return. What did you learn?

With your assistance, I can focus on preparations for the coming plague. I wish I could be of more help, but I'm afraid I don't have much to offer.nnMy advice? Keep your eyes open and talk to the villagers.
Our guar barns are south of here. Burn the barrel of brandy, get his attention, and butcher him like the animal he is.nnThen bring me the antidote so that I can save my mother. Please!
The Vereansu camp is just outside the village. Follow the path in front of the temple and it will take you there. Take a torch from their bonfire and set their supply crates ablaze!
Leel-Vata is my second sun. She gives me light and warmth in a world that is all too often cold and grim.nnPlease, see her back to me safely.
Make his death quick, please. He is still my egg-brother.
The acolytes await. Get moving. I doubt they have the fortitude to remain in position for long.
The Daedra you will face are fearsome. Be prepared.
Please get the antidote to Lady Drathyra.nnQuickly, before Matriarch Saalu passes!
Is it true that Matriarch Saalu is dead?nnSomeone must tell Lord garvas. You should speak to him at the main house, along the road north of the sulfer pools.
Arrogant dryskin! Meddling in the affairs of the Saxhleel.
It's true. I was cowering here, but I was hoping you would survive the entire time.nnUm, did you learn how to bind Balreth?
Defend the hall!
We're in the heart of the cave, friend. Now is the time to strike.nnWhat do you say? Think we're mighty enough to take on the Goblin Warlord and his spider queen?
Go! Go! Don't worry about me. Get the Tear!
Shor's bones, you have to help! nnAggh. Miserable Gobs.
Back so soon? I wouldn't expect it could be quite that simple.
The guardians are in place. Good.nnNow we can finish this.
You have the antidote for Saalu?nnPlease, make for the western cave with all speed.
Ah, you again! I'm sure there are uses for your skills here.
Martin's my older brother, so I've looked up to him ever since I was just a child. nnSomehow, someday, I know he's going to change his ways, whatever path he chooses in life.
Well done, my friend. Now where's <<1>>? My axe thirsts for his blood.
Well met, friend. What brings you to Fork Virak?
Make your way through the broken wall, my wispy friend. Find a way to unlock the door from the other side.
Our guar are scattered throughout the sulfur pools to the south.nnThey won't return without the reminder of a harness around their necks. And dead guar don't need harnesses anymore.
I knew a woman would successfully navigate the Coiled Path.
Our fate rests in your hands.

Frankly, I'm surprised the Shornhelm Guard is willing to take on such riff-raff. nnIf Martin doesn't take the deal Captain Thayer's offering, he deserves to rot in the stocksfor dull wittedness, if nothing else.
You'll really collect the graven caps I need?nnThank you, traveler.
I see you returned, but with empty hands. We're only going to get so many chances, so be more careful this time.
Did you tell Bala to come to me? I wonder where she is?nnI can't wait. This will be so amusing!
I wonder if that stupid Ashlander got lost. Perhaps one of the guardians murdered her.nnEanen, that lowborn is leering at me. Kill it or something!
Why are you here? Go to Rhavil's house. nnEven now, that Covenant witch may be warning him that he's been found out.
Listen. You need to let me out of here. Don't tell anyone, and I'll make sure that you get rewarded. Just let me and my wife leave for Mournhold.
It seems we have proof that the Dres are trying to murder our tree.
Good luck in your travels, warm-blood.
Thank the three you're here, we desperately need your help.
Almalexia bless you for getting those people to safety. nnNow head back to Merarii. By now, she doubtless has some new idea of how to deal with this curse.
My sister returned to me right before House Redoran arrived.
There's nothing more to be said. Please do this for me, stranger.
I'm going to pull myself together and get out of here.nnI'll see you outside, Vivec willing.
What happened in there? This whole situation makes me very curious.
I'll stay out of your way. Just don't hurt me!
Hold it right there. This is Duke Nathaniel's personal library. No access without his express permission.

The entrance to the ruins is beyond the northern gates. Look for a strange door set in the mountain wall.nnMadras and the others went on ahead, but you should be able to catch them. I'm sure they'd welcome your help.
If you get taken by the Maulborn, don't come to us for help. I'm sure House Hlaalu will save you.
It looks like the rats are moving in.nnI appreciate your help in this. Now no one will get hurt.
I don't believe we have anything else to discuss.nnYou're on your own. Good hunting.
The merchant now serves the Ghost Snake. It's an honor, though he probably doesn't appreciate it.
Hrmph! Well, you're not half-bad, I'll give you that.
I  can't hold him  much longer. Use the altar now!
Woof! Ha ha ha! Good fight! nnYou'll have to find someone else to brawl with. I just need a moment to catch my breath. And stop the bleeding. And get another mead. You know how it is.
Do you have the reagents?
<<1>> made a <<2>>? Great!nnCan you use it to help the survivors?
What have you decided to do?
I've never heard of anything like this happening in a kwama mine before.
You are on your way to becoming an extraordinary smith <<1>>.  nnYour next step is mastering some more recipes in order to qualify to take your journeyman test. nnLuckily I have some for sale.
I can feel the blessings upon you. It's a power I've not felt myself for many years.
What are you doing down here?
I saw that Covenant captain making for the gate. That was kind of you. In fact, you were kinder than I might have been.
I sense change. The curse retreats, broken. You've succeeded?
The souls are assembled. It is well.nnTalk to <<1>>. Then we'll begin.
All is prepared.nnTalk to <<1>>. Then we'll begin.

Varon and I will work on a cure, but meanwhile I need you to destroy the shipments. We can't let the plague reach Mournhold.nnRendezvous with the archers. They're outside the top of the cave, on an overlook.
Hold there. Visitors to Tal'Deic Fortress must adhere to protocol. We have very strict rules here.
Find the missing scouts. We'll need every blade in our attack on the Maulborn.
Thank you for choosing the Foozle. Please, hand it over now.
The clarity with which two words appear in your head is astounding, "Piss off."
Don't worry about me, I'll be fine. A little scrape won't kill me.nnI'd feel better if I got some of my cargo back, along with the manifest. The raiders captured it, took it up the hill.
I knew you'd help us. May the Three guide your weapons.

Fear not, we're the same people we were before we gained this  affliction.nnYears ago, a terrible sickness swept through our lands. I had to do something to keep my people safe. It's why I made a deal with the Daedra.
Raston never returned. I'm not sure how long we'll stay here.
Tarry no longer. The vicecanons await your introduction in the Guild Hall.
I didn't know <<1>>, but <<2>> named him a good man. Damn these murders!
I'll be waiting in the stables. Try not to get murdered.
I don't Tiril
<<1>> thinks we can learn something from the Worm Cultists, but I know fanatics when I see them.
Find their commander in the camp east of town. Make them understand the error of crossing House Dres. Be my hand of vengeance!
Rescue the grandmaster's son. With Sen Dres free, we can retake Kragenmoor from the Vanguard.
Nothing would please me more than the deaths of all these necromancers.nnI might tell you why later.
Go tell Ulov to meet me in the stables. Then use that totem at the altar near the pumpkin patch.nnWhether the monster is killed or not doesn't matter to me. My life is done.
The Trial of the Mind begins in the chamber below.
You've passed the trials. It's a rare thing you've accomplished.
<<1>> will know what to do, I'm sure of it.
You bear the Hist amber? Then you must rouse Hissmir's true power. The Zaht stones await you.
You are on your way to becoming an extraordinary smith <<1>>.  nnYour next step is mastering some more recipes in order to qualify to take your journeyman test. nnLuckily I have some for sale.
You're on your way to becoming an extraordinary smith. nnTo progress to the level of journeymen I need you to learn a few more recipes, gather more materials, and practice your craft.

I'm very proud of you, apprentice. Seldom do I get the chance to work with someone so talented and fire-resistant.nnYou need to do a little more work before I can consider you a journeyman. I have some recipes. Purchase them, learn them, craft them.
I can't believe you brought Omalor out for us.nnOh, I'm going to enjoy this.
Many have died upon the Coiled Path. Likely, you will die, too.
Why are you still here? I can't keep <<(MONSTER:20112>> from her soul gems forever. nnIf you want futher training, I suggest you go to Mournhold. The runecrafters there are said to be sane.
Banishing a dro-m'Athra is as hard as calling it. Once you've empowered the totem with dead spirits, speak to Ruvali. nnRa-shadda must speak to her first. This one must see what can be said.

I'm very proud of you, apprentice. Seldom do I get the chance to work with someone so talented and fire-resistant.nnYou need to do a little more work before I can consider you a journeyman. I have some recipes. Purchase them, learn them, craft them.
Last-to-Water's not a kind or loving father, but he's family. Loyalty does not end when the egg cracks.nnPlease rescue him.
Thanks for coveringI mean, thanks for getting me out of that cage so I could wreak havoc on the Maulborn.
Saryvn here has told me an interesting story. Care to elaborate?
The flies are the worst. It's not the bites. It's the incessant buzzing.nnI'll go mad by the time I get out of these shackles.
You're on your way, apprentice. The next step is journeyman. To reach that bend in the river, you must learn more recipes. Craft more items.nnI have some scrolls here, if you need a push.
I'll remain here to protect what relics are left. To guard these pieces of our heritage  such a strange thought.
You haven't introduced yourself, outsider. I don't care if you're brave or foolish. Don't waste my valuable time.nnState your purpose. Why should you stand before One-Eye?
Be careful in those ruins. No telling who these mysterious others may be.
Where have you been? Where's the General?
What do you want? Can't you see I'm busy?
I fear something horrible has happened to those poor travelers.
Learned the recipe?
Be prepared, outsider. The Sentinels fight to win.
Beatings, extortion, taking whatever they damn well please. Someone should stand up to those thugs.
You're favored by the Ghost Snake, outsider. Did you find the eggs?

You're carrying a great deal of medicine. That's good, but I have no use for it here.nnYou'll need to go south. Give the supplies to the farseer within Iliath Temple. She'll tell you what to do with them.
That High Elf won't wait forever. Get in there before she suspects anything.
The vicecanons won't do anything. I can't believe it!
You're back! And you're not full of stinger holes.
I hope you found Gethis. None of this should happen to such a good man.
Choose well, traveler.
You'll find the keystone within the Temple of Sul. You must obtain it before the Dominion.
Time we get to work, yes? Won't be long until the Dominion learns Tsanji is dead. Then they'll take their treasure and run.nnThat's bad for both of us.
Remember, just taking the resonators isn't enough. You also need to disable the repair stations.
Whoever's behind the murders appears to be resourceful. Take care you don't end up the next victim.
It doesn't have to end like this. Not with another slaughter. Not with more blood between us.
It's the stomach juices! Brings out the properties of the fronds. You see, wamasu are not strictly carnivorous. So, when one chews on this leaf like so .
Welcome. I've heard we've you to thank for ridding <<1>> of those Imperials.nnI'm glad to see you're paying us a visit.

Now that you have a writ from the Great Moot you should study your profession under your new master. It will be hard, no doubt about it. Stick to it and you might mean the difference between success and defeat in Cyrodil!
<<1>> and I are going to rest before we brave the road to Mud Tree.nnMaybe you should rest, too. You don't look so well.

Ah, you're a brave person, right? I mean, that's what people say. I'm Sonding and I guess  I mean I don't know  maybe you can help. nnEveryone here is too focused on kidnappings and murders to listen to me, but I'm sure it's important.
You've seen me up here, writing? Letters sent, but not returned. Why do I keep writing to him if he doesn't care?nnPerhaps the mire has finally taken him. I've been sending letters to a corpse.
May the Three watch over you. From what I've been hearing, if anyone could find our missing vicecanon, it's you.
The Pact thanks you for joining the war effort! With talented crafters like yourself at our back, there's no challenge we can't overcome.nnAkatosh bless your wares, friend.
Get the recipe from <<1>>. Once you learned it talk to me
Excellent! I see my companions have assembled. Now, we can open the portal to the ritual chamber. Just let me know when you are ready.
You must summon the guardians. We'll handle the scamps. We'll meet you at the top. nnWalks-in-Ash should already be there. She's always been a stealthy sort.
The wind has carried you here with your scales unburnt.nnWhat do we do now?
Shor's bones! nnClosing those caves saved lives! We're all in your debt.
Once she has grown bored with her Altmer lover, she'll discard him for another. nnAnd like a man-eating beast, she has grown a taste for mortal attentions.
You've caused enough trouble!nn<<1>> will hear of this! You were sent here to upset my wife! Begone, before I lose my temper.
Have you crafted the ring?
The acolytes await your assistance. Speak to them as soon as you can. I fear for their safety.
We're not dead. Amazing!nnI need a little time to recover. Go speak to Vaama and get that other Daedric essence.
That worked! And no strange side effects.nnQuickly now. Go to the other ruin and speak to <<1>>.
We are gathering the essences of these Daedra. Speak with the acolytes. They know how to summon them.
Your help dealing with those Supernal Dreamers was greatly appreciated.
Thanks again for your help, friend.
Thanks again for recovering the shards.  My wizard says it will be mended soon.
I see you rescued my son. He is a good boy, if a bit incapable.
Thanks for returning my crystal. You have no idea how much that thing is worth. Certainly more than you'll ever earn in your life.
The cave ahead is probably the best approach, as the path to the north goes through the center of the Hollow and right into the thick of Vox's forces. nnDestroy the three wards, blessed one!
Have you crafted the ring?
Speak to my father. He's been asking for you.

How many of those torchbug-gobblers did you flatten? I bet it was half a dozen.nnWait, you still have the <<z:1>>? Quick, get it to Chieftain Suhlak! If Clavicus Vile lifts his curse while you still hold it, you'll die for good!
Hurry to the Tribunal Temple. Don't keep the Sacred Lady waiting.
I'm terribly sorry, I can't spend more time chatting. There are a lot of people waiting for registration who don't have the same clout as you do.
You showed those Wood Elf rats? Now we are the proud owners of this treasure!nnWell, us and a few others.
Vivec's trial will measure your clarity of judgment. He saw our blessed people through vexing times. His wisdom reveals the secrets others keep.nnSo shall yours be put to the test.
I'm sure one of the other aides told you to talk to <<1>>. He's in the center of town.nnIt's the way we do things here, stranger.
You look new here, stranger. I hope one of the other aides directed you to speak with <<1>>.nnYou can find him in the center of town.
Wha  was I sleeping? I saw an Argonian waif, crying for help.nnMy head feels like it's trying to leave my body. I need to sit down.
You've made us proud today.
Head to the front line. See what you can find. We'll speak when you return.
Welcome to the Daggerfall Mages Guild. What can I do for you on this day blessed by the Eight?
Those Elven blackguards deserve every bit of trouble that comes to them.
I  where am I? Do you hear it? The voice is gone. It's gone!nnBy the Lord General's sword! How long was I out?
How did I get this far into the ruins?nnThe goblin totem! Where is it? I need it!
I  I am awake, aren't I? This is real. Isn't it?
You've got the missing stone fragments? Let's see if we can activate it, then. You go ahead.
You're surprised  or frightened. It's difficult for me to determine which.
I can't believe our guards were slain by the Worm Cult! How will we make it safely to Mud Tree?
If those guards were slain by the Worm Cult, their spirits must be freed. I shudder to think of what those necromancers will do with them.
You are kind. I don't think every sister tests her brother this way, but it has always been so with me and Pash-Riha.
Seven-Bellies would be pleased if I crawled back into an egg. Then he could sit on it and protect me.nnHis concern is not lost on me, but after I hatched, I'd still bite his tail.
Follow the gorge to the east and climb to the ruins. nnFight well.
You've done much to help us, but all may yet be undone.nnThe storage tunnel is just behind the temple. Seek out <<1>>. He'll be leading the defense. Help him keep our enemies at bay.
Welcome to the Fighters Guild! You look like the capable sort. Why have you come? Are you here to answer the Guildmaster's challenge?
Good luck in there. Remember, don't let anyone see you!
My favorite <<1>>! Were these different times I'd see you well fed and laughing. Lukiul Uxith was once quite a place.nnYou have something to tell me?
Let me take these goods back to my family, so they don't starve.
I hope my loose guar aren't causing any trouble.nnKeep it up! There are a few more out there.
The yard is secure. Once again, the Pact controls Fort Virak. nnYet <<1>> still lives. Where is he? He has much to answer for.
If you can find that bow, <<1>> would appreciate it.
What are you waiting for? Light the fire.
Good thing you came along when you did. I'm pretty sure they were preparing more unconventional methods of extracting information, if you know what I mean.
This is beyond what we usually handle. But the Shadowscales are up for any task.
We don't understand the full power of the keystones. Even one might give the Dominion terrible power.
If you're willing, I have another task for you.
Without you, we'd have been food for the <<mz:1>>.
The Dominion still hasn't found the keystone, you should still be able to swipe it under their nose.
I do believe this is our best work yet.

Got your pickaxe? Head into the Ashlanders' tunnel and use it to weaken the supports. We'll hold them off here.nnI won't wish you good luck. Only children and Altmer rely on it. I'd rather trust in your skill.
Dolril's safe, at least. Thank you for returning him to us.nnNow there's nothing to do but wait for these Ashlanders to grow tired of killing and leave.
Yes? What it is?
I heard fighting below. Are you all right?
I said I would turn the stuff in and I will. Though I still think it's a waste.
You threaten Vox, enraging her, forcing her to commit even more brutal atrocities! How glorious!nnSoon her army of Daedra and lost souls will march forth, unleashing new terrors across the land.
I never liked bugs. Now I positively hate them!
As I said, the other vicecanons broke away at the first sign of fighting. I don't know where those spineless cowards are, but we need to regroup if we're going to have a chance at this.
<<1>> was a sight to see, coming out of that cave. She makes a pretense of frailty, but she stood shoulder to shoulder with the rest of her troops. Such valiance is a rare trait in politicians.
Thank you for stopping <<1>>'s imposter. He deserved no less.
Can't  move! Help me!
Uhhh, uhhh!
My arms and legs won't work! Sep's blood, I don't want to be eaten by baby snakes!
Argh! It burns! It burns!
Just remember, this doesn't make us partners!
Ssethreka has this place in her coils. Her scales must be shorn and her fangs blunted!
No sign of <<1>>, but the Nord over there is definitely a skin-stealer. I know what he's planning to do with those prisoners. If I help out, you'll tell nobody about my Daedric relic-hunting, yes?
Now that you're here, we'll take the fight to the mountain. To Tanval.
The gatekeeper is the only thing standing in our way.
That faithless harlot! How dare she hone in on my deal!
You've completed my trial, mortal. Seek my colleague on the stairs above the caldera.
You're no fool to withhold your trust. Commendable, truly. But you'll go no further without my help.nnDestroy these bindings and free me!
I can sense the spirits with you, my friend.
Did the spirits talk to you? What did they say?
Find a way to kill <<1>> and I'll reward you handsomely.
Ho there! Shanked anyone lately?
My mother and brother are safe, and I have you to thank. Praise the Three they survived.
To duel is a blessing. It separates truth from untruth, yes?
No! Not fathernnHe was the best man I ever knew.
No words but her words!
Back away, outsider.
You're the help <<1>> sent? Looks like he finally did something right.nnWelcome. I'm Saervild Steel-Wind, Vicecanon Hrondar's deputy.
That can't have been an easy decision. Prisoners freed into the fens? Who knows what they'll do with their freedom?nnI received a message. The Dominion finally made their move against <<1>>.
I was trapped. I let myself get trapped. Perhaps I would even be dead. You changed that, friend.nnUnderstand: I'm grateful, but I also wish you had never found me.
You grow used to the ointment's smell after a while. You didn't get any in your eyes, did you? Good, good.
Made it out alive, I see. How did it go?
We're too late. The keepers have fallen.
Did you talk to Mavos?
Are you insane? Don't you know what taking those relics will do to the dreugh?
She speaks. She speaks!
We finally made it. I thought we were done for, once or twice.nnBefore you take the keystone, there's something you must know.
I think we have all the pieces. Place the skull with them to restore the reliquary.

Amazing work, my friend. Now Dithis and I can deconstruct the goblinization matrix and see where I went wrong. Perhaps some sort of magical attraction component was added by mistake. nnSo Dithis  do you feel pretty?
I've decided to leave Dithis as a Goblin for a few days. Hopefully, it will remind the brothers of what happens when they meddle in magic they don't understand.
I can't thank you enough for saving me from <<1>>. I'm going to suffer through this humiliation as long as I need to. At least I'm alive!nnAnd stop looking at me like that, Denthis.
Assistant, you know better than to .nnYes, I think I see. What brings you to me, "Assistant?"
Please, we must take the eggs to safety!
You can't fight all the spirits here. Subdue a few. The rest may follow.
The box appears to be in fine condition.nnMay I?
The urge to plunge your hand in fire, to spill your own blood? My whisper in your ear, supplicant. Know that I made you the instrument of my will.
My cat wouldn't leave Ebonheart, I know he's here somewhere. If you find him, please bring him home!
I'm dry with apprehension, comrade. Everywhere, I smell musty rot.nnIt is different than the rot of the swamp. It makes my scales itch.
We haven't heard from my brother yet. I hope he is well.
Ah, my friend from Davon's Watch!. Interested in more work?nnI've located another rare vintage here in Ebonheart.
Find all of those bones and make sure they cannot be used. Bakkhara has faith in you.
Speak to the grandmaster if you truly wish to help us.
Don't worry about me. Plenty more must die before my revenge is complete.
If you can get this mess sorted out we'll be back to business as usual and I won't have to listen to any more of <<1>>'s moaning.
Comrade, I'm glad you're going with <<1>>. Her passion to discover Doshia's goal is all-consuming. I fear it will cloud her judgement. nnStendarr watch over you both.

Who knows what <<1>> thought she was after? What clawless fool records her plan in a journal?nnAelif would like to point out that the Dwarves believed in nothing. What would they know of Molag Bal's plot?
You'll be in good hands with Merric. he's one of our best men, and an ardent soldier against the daedra.
We must stop the daedra from invading, no matter what the means.
I don't care what you do to the Wood Orcs. Do whatever it takes to stop my sister from going down this path.
You're looking for the keystone?nnI can tell you with absolute certainty it's not here.
How fares the hunt?
Here, take the antidote. Keep it close. Don't use it unless you feel her poison take effect.
Lost your spider? Vivec's sake. Go get another one.
You heard Merric, new blood. Search those bodies. Aelif will check this one.
Let's get out of this hell hole.
Damn  Merric
You've done a lot for the Fighters Guild. We will contact you as soon as we've deciphered this journal.
I wonder if Sees-All-Colors knows what she's gotten herself into. Molag Bal is a formidable opponent. This war has just begun.
Praise the Hist. You return safely! You have something with our enemy's scent?
You smell terrible, like those runty Wood Elves.
Now that Vox's forces are weakened, victory is within our grasp.
Be careful down there, friend. The dead are about in great numbers, doing the things that the living dead do. I don't expect you can reason with them.
Thank you for releasing me, but you should not linger.
Welcome back. Something I can do for you?
The Shadowscales want the Fangs of Sithis! There are so many of them .nnBut they're dangerous. The Fangs in the hands of assassins? I can't imagine anything worse.
Someone infiltrated the Shadowscales. I wonder .
You've got more guts than I have.
My assignments keep getting worse and worse.
Well done. Now that the portals are closed, we can clean up the remaining invaders.
After prayers, we'll clear out the remaining Daedra.
You've done the Guild proud, comrade.
I'm so glad to be out of there. Thank Stendarr you saved me from that vile creature.
I will pray to our master for your victory.nnTo Hermaeus Mora, He Who Holds the Paper to the Light!
Ready?
I am Jack's default greeting.
What do you want?
The Eye glares. The master calls for retribution.
I exist to serve. I can ferry you to Shad Astula whenever you are ready.
He's betrayed the clutch. How can we trust him after this?
Father is going to have a hard time explaining this.
Search the library below and find the librarian. She hasn't responded to my calls.nnI fear something foul stalks my Academy.
Good luck, traveler.
I really owe you one.nnIf you get some free time, maybe we can meet for lunch or something.
Send it away! Send it away!
Hadmar will stay here for a while. It's not safe out there and I don't want to have my mind controlled. No, no, no.
Thanks for getting that <<1>>. Catch up with me at Ebonheart.nnI heard that another, shall we say, "collectible" wine is there.
Continue your journey, wherever your path leads.nnWe'll contact you once we know more.
We'll figure this out in time. Speak carefully. Let no one hear anything we've planned.
Comrade, we must restore this weapon of old. Make ready for any new plots by the Prince of Lies. I feel the strength of Stendarr flowing through my arms. Are you prepared?
We'll leave once we've packed our things.
Cast Carethil out before it's too late.
Everything's ready for the blessing. All I need is the <<1>>, and then we can start.
You are ready to go back?
Why hasn't he come home? Where can he be?
Welcome to the hall, comrade! I bet you've got some good tales to tell of our war on the Anchors.
You brought my sweet Rulantaril to his senses.nnThank you, mortal. Now we can be together, forever and ever.
Don't eat any cooked trodh, Lukiul. Just tell me everything you hear about the sacred performance.nnAnd ignore anything you hear about a secret society, or a death sentence.
Which toll will you choose to pay? Toll of flesh hurts flying rats. Toll of silver makes us richer. Pay, pay!
You radiate an aura of power. Does this mean you have the books?
Be careful. <<1>> is not to be taken lightly. I lost the sanctuary because of his nimble tongue and mad stare.
Well, what is it? Here for some noble purpose, no doubt.
You! Our knave tells me you have chosen to pay the toll of silver! What say you?
An outsider in the Blackfeather Court. You must pay the toll!
The featherless one approaches.
Back work, it seems. I guess that's an improvement.
Tell Not-So-Quick he shouldn't drink the elixir.nnI know. Trust me.
Ow. I don't feel so good.
Kyne's breath! You've done it.
Not bad! All right, now I know the melody. What are the lyrics to this fancy song, mead demon?
So many proud warriors slain. We'll repay every drop of blood threefold.
The way is clear. Please, find the foreman. We'll hold the mine entrance and the town.
I don't mind chatting with you, but I'm sure you've got other things to do.
How goes the murder?
Say, I think you told me a whopper.
Stop <<1>> before it is to late.
I do hope you have success in killing Remelie.nnShe's had plenty of success in killing my guards.
As long as the Twilight Boss still lives we are all still in danger.
Ah, there you are. Took you long enough.
Here is your well-deserved reward.
<cough> Kill the beast or we will never be free from the threat of the Dreamers.
Shor's bones, I'm glad you're here. Look for my miners while you're exploring. They don't deserve this.
Please, help me!
I thought I was dead. Please, free me.
I don't want to die down here. What will my brother do without me?
The Reach are animals. Get me out of here!
I'll meet you at the tavern in Riften as soon as I can, my new friend.
Thanks for saving us! Good luck out there!
I don't care about <<1>> and her mine. I'm marching up to that camp, killing every Goblin I can find, and getting Hodmar's body back.nnI'll see his bones back in Skyrim or die trying.
<<1>> and I are going to rest before we brave the road to Mud Tree.nnMaybe you should rest, too. You don't look so well.
I'm almost afraid to touch <<A:1>>. Are we too late?
Let's wreak some havoc!
The thought of <<1>> alone in these ruins concerns me. She's no summer hatchling.nnDon't tell her I said that.
What happened? Where did you go?
Quick, give me the totem. I'll use it to lead the Goblins into the swamps. They won't bother anyone after that.nnSure, they're not civilized, but they don't deserve this abuse.
What happened to the vicecanon?
Thanks for saving me back there. Whatever you did, <<1>> was not pleased. Not pleased at all. Did you recover the keystone?
Please take whatever you've found to Garm.nnOnce he's gone, I'm sure things will return to normal.
Help me, please. My partner is trapped in the mine! I can't bear the thought of anything happening to Adana down there.
You've found others, but not <<1>>? Don't give up, I can't bear the thought of continuing without him!
My sister is trapped in the mine! Raena is all I have left, after our father fell fighting the Reachmen. Please rescue her!
The keeper wants everything perfect for the hatching.

<<1>> already has your reward all counted out and ready to hand over.nnYou give me the totem, we go back to work, and these Goblins learn from the example of the Ebonheart Pact. That's better for all of us.
If anyone can work out how to end these  abominations, it's Belron.
<This cultist was killed recently. The body is still warm.>
With the shroud gone, we can follow you in!nnYou're looking a little dead around the edges. Let me take care of that.
Look for my fiancee, <<1>>. I've been away on business, and came home to this! I do not know if she lives or fell prey to one of those things!
Kill the Pact to end the act. Ha! I did it again, didn't I?
This is a once in a lifetime opportunity! Thank you for making this possible, my friend.nnNow let's move! This ruin isn't going to study itself!
You're Kyne-sent, traveler. Please.
While many fell today, many more would have fallen if it weren't for you, but you must make it to the Signal Tower to warn the rest of the Rift of Sinmur's return and that Reachman army!
This great furry horker didn't go down easily.nnAll I could think of were my girls.
My sister ran into the cave. Hurry!
Follow Father. We'll be right behind you.
Shalidor found you. Excellent. At long last, I've been able to translate the book you recovered.nnAre you prepared to accept Sheogorath's first challenge?
Valaste awaits you at the Guildhall in Daggerfall, along the southern coast of Glenumbra.
Oh, my poor Tavo! What am I going to do without him?
I already owe you. But I'm hearing rumors. They need to be investigated.
I sense the <<1>> banished, but only for a trice. He shall return to mete out weighty punishment. nnI cannot destroy <<Az:2>>, but I beseech you do so. End the source of the <<1>>'s hold upon us!
I hope my daughter Milta is still alive.
<<1>> can't seem to decide whether to come home or not. Could you talk to him?
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
My brother still has not returned. I fear the Goblins did not greet him as he expected.
I fear my brother's idealism got the better of him. He still hasn't returned from the Goblin camp.
Thanks to you, we'll be able to heal all of the wounded. We are in your debt.
Isn't it beautiful? The most beautiful part of the chateau. You can see why I've held onto the place all these years.
Light that fire, soldier!
It's no use. Unless they're whole, the spirits of the departed can receive no comfort.
Don't be fooled by appearances. Trust what the amulet shows you!
I'm going to have to head back to town soon, my friend. Lost a lot of blood.nnHow goes the hunt?
Skyshroud Barrows is northeast of the village. Send everyone you find back here. Good luck.
You should be able to get them out before they're a meal for spiders.nnWe shouldn't have come here. I should have listened to the guildmaster.
The undead are gone. What did you do?
May Arkay see us through these troubled times.
I stand once more at the seat of my power. I am a spectre, a mere shade, forced to watch as a necromancer defiles my body.nnKill him.
Damned necromancers and their crystals.
I feel like an idiot for trusting Ulrich so completely. I know better now.
Why are you still talking to me?
Two switches will shut these traps off. We need to hit them at the same time. nnGet the one on the far wall. I'll hit mine when you do.
According the spirit, you'll need to collect the north, south, and central runestones to gain access to Skyshroud Crater.
I can't thank you enough for saving me. I'm no milk drinker, but those bandits could have sent me to Sovngarde with the flick of a wrist.
You haven't found all of them? Please keep looking, I know they're out there.
Goblins are pathetic beasts, but they have their uses.

Shalidor found you, excellent. I've puzzled out the hints from that last book  and I'm afraid the news isn't good. Your next trial is in a particularly nasty part of the Shivering Isles. A place called the Chateau of the Ravenous Rodent.
They're here! They're inside my heart and my head and my eyes! I can see them with all three!
<<<1>> makes a sad sound as he looks to the south.>
If Vantir's dead, please tell Diodore. No matter what I've said, he's nervous as a foal.
Watch out for the bandits' wolves. They'll sniff you out in a second.
I'll be honest, adept. I can barely stand to look at you. Sending an intelligent woman like Valaste off with that creature. But  I feel honor bound to offer you a final gift.
Ah! Good! You and I can have reasonable conversations. Shalidor's just too old and crotchety for me.
It is good Bera found you, comrade. The Bright Moons know Aelif is glad to see you again. She would trust no one else for the task before us today.
My work here is nearly complete, comrade. The core will soon be a weapon once again.
A Daedric titan is a formidable foe. They are the living siege engines of Molag Bal's invasion force. That you overcame one is testament to your strength.
While waiting to set sail is a thrill, please complete your business and let the captain know we're ready to go.
How did this happen? More importantly, what's happening to the vicecanon?nnI'm at a loss. What do we do now?
Head into the fort. Defend it from Covenant attackers.nnKyne watch your hide, friend.
Have you closed the master portal yet?
I know, I know. You're not going to be yourself again until we find your <<1>>, but don't go back out there!
Please, find the others.
So grateful for your help. Keep up the search.
The others are on the edge of the dagger. Please.
I hope you have put many Daggers into the earth.
I'd just speak to him and get it over with. I don't trust him, but I'm sure he'll do you no harm.nnYou are, after all, his instrument for the moment.
What a bloody, tragic business!
Violence is one of my favorite forms of madness.
Good choice.
Violence is one of my favorite forms of madness.
Comrade, I put my life in your hands. What is to be my fate?
I love it when a plan comes together!nnReally, you'd think forest spirits wouldn't be so greedy with their things.
You're back? They told you, didn't they? About their plotting?nnThey can't have it. They'll never have it!
Finally patched the old girl up! Can't wait to get out on the water again.
Thank you so much! I hope Thulvald enjoys my company, even though we're very different.
Thank you again. If the conscripts remember your lessons, we might just make it through this.
Thank you again. Did you know she likes my branches  er, that is, my arms?nnJust don't mention flowering buds. She blushed and slapped me when I brought it up.
How are the bees? The success of the meadery depends on their honey. It has to be perfect!
He left us no choice.
Kazok's head stuck on a pike will give the remaining Stormfists in the area something to think about!
For the glory of Yorgrim!
I see you found the meat. Please put it to good use.
Collect one of the General's hairs and find a way to slip the sleep potion into his drink. I'll start preparing for the ritual.
Give Skorvild the lamb meat instead. That should hamper his dark ritual.
I didn't think you'd survive, but here you are.
Stay moist, comrade.nnYou'll hear from us once we've decoded the journal.
Be careful on that island, hero. Aelif will report the situation to the boss lady.
I hope you're finding my <<1>> useful. nnLet me know how well they work for you.
Are you executing a contract at the moment?nnHeh. Executing.
Make sure you try some of Roruld's special batch. That's some damn fine mead!
Search around the house for a way in. I don't think you'll find a key under a rock, but you never know.nnI'll make sure this location is secure. Then I'll meet you over there as soon as I can.
Be careful on that island, hero. Aelif will report the situation to the boss lady.
Were you able to light the fires? That's the only way to warn Davon's Watch.
You radiate an aura of power. Does this mean you have the books?
You radiate an aura of power. Does this mean you have the books?
Those wolf pelts were very helpful. It's good to know that even vicious monsters can be useful after they're killed and skinned.

Kyne sent us a miracle, friend.nnThe witches barged in and I thought we were going to have to fight them. But they started tending to our wounds! They helped us and walked away. I don't understand any of this.
You only have two things left to do. One: find Keeper Ormi. Two: put a blade in her dark heart.nnIf that doesn't end the curse, at least it will make damn certain no one else gets bewitched.
I'll make sure no other travelers fall victim to the dark witches.nnWindhelm will send troops to wipe them out. I give you my word.
We'll make things right. You'll see.
Let's get out of this hell hole.
Did the Fighters Guild send you? Has word reached the guild hall?
I'm glad I found you, Comrade. The guild has need of your  unique talents.
Hurry! To the Hall of Trials! You must protect King Jorunn at all costs.
Disgusting bug dog! Gena, are you sure you want to keep it?
There's no scent of the dead on you. Please hurry and check out that graveyard.
Thank you again. I actually think this has been good for me.nnIf you can't tame your own fear, how can you tame anything else?
A good race, but you were outclassed. Still, I'm always happy to see someone new perform so admirably.
Where's my banner? You promised to get it for me!
Perhaps you should pay more attention to the task at hand.
Perhaps you should pay more attention to the task at hand.
You brought my Crystal back.  Why are you still talking to me?
Can I help you, soldier?
My own brother and the traitorous Stormfist clan? Here?nnI won't stand for this! Guards!
Were the Orcthane's agents dealt with?
Discover anything new about your mark?
Well, now we may be onto something, you've been looking around pretty well.
Now you're talking, looks like you have a line on this guy.
I'm sure Thane Mera will appreciate your assistance. And your discretion.
You haven't found all of them? Please keep looking, I know they're out there.
Perhaps a bit more intrigue will help. No, too many threads already.
Go after her! You may be our last hope at retelling the story!
You've returned? Does this mean <<1>> is safe?
I hope my father can attend the council meeting.

We finally decided to disobey Spinner Indinael, and it's a good thing we did! Endrith and I saw the cultists carrying a body inside the cave, here.nnWe have no weapons! We can't fight the least of the undead, let alone the cultists!
My death is the beginning of a new story, and not a happy one, I fear.nnI feel the pulse of the Worm Cult. I must resist.
target: My death is the beginning of a new story, and not a happy one, I fear.nnI feel the pulse del Culto del Verme. I must resist.

source: Spinner Indinael needs help!
Well played! Now place the offerings on the altar behind me.
You came just in time! Eveline would have been furious if I died.
Lucky you came along when you did! We've got a lot of work to do.
Farewell.
You know, this isn't the gift I expected you to bring back. An Imperial? Really?
The Emissary of Z'en! My prayers are answered! She'll strike down the Drublog and end all of this!
All this blood and violence. By the Nine Holds, I need a drink.
I can't wait for the bard to sing a song. Isn't he handsome?
The bard returned, telling a strange tale about an enchanted lute. He seemed quite distraught.
Keep your head down, or the Worms will take you away and you'll never be seen again!
You must enter the crypt beneath my father's manor and put an end to his plots and schemes.

As soon as I get this lift working, I'll meet you down there. Just watch out for the constructs. These ruins are always full of constructs.nnAnd if you spot the lore vault, please tell Kireth. That's what she's down there looking for.
This is now your story, wherein you saved Malabal Tor.
And so the story ends, mortal. Your part in the balance won't be forgotten.
That bard returned. The tale he told us was frightening, but he had good things to say about you.
This place will never be the same again.
Fascinating. Batrachite's hold on this plane weakens, and a mortal is responsible. You may prove useful.
I'm very sorry about what happened.
I never asked for this, any of this. Why can't I live as I choose?
The story came close to destruction thanks to the Hound's interference.nnAnd now, he can never change a story as ageless as that of the Silvenar and the Green Lady.
Did you come here to learn about the life of the Green Lady?
What do you think? We've only got the one orb you found.
You look like you need a bear steak. Charred on the outside, bloody in the middle!
Remember, after you get the goat to follow you, lead it back here to me.

We need to attract Rilis' attention, and retaking the binding stone that was his prison is sure to alert him.  It's just up ahead.nnMount an assault to secure the stone and he's sure to make an appearance. Defeat Rilis, and we will contain him.
Sounds like you have orders from another ranking officer, my friend. Get going.
Greetings in his name. Always happy to have new faces join us. Especially from Hammerfell!

Find my son and end his life. And do it quickly.nnThe power I gave should aid you in the coming battle. Valeric may not be as strong as I am, but my blood runs through his veins. Underestimate him at your own peril.
I can't believe I slept through the whole thing.
The way is clear, friend of the Silvenar!
Well met, champion.
They're  the tribes assembled. Too much for us.
They're killing our neighbors. Of course they deserve to pay with their heads. And any other parts of their bodies you feel like separating.
If you have nothing to do, talk to <<1>>. Try to avoid bothering those who are busy.
My thanks.
What I wouldn't give for the power to kill that raving bastard!nnHe's been watching us, and mentions the Daedra to mock me. How glorious it would be to turn them against him, use the Daedra for good.
I wish you luck and I hope you can save your king. May the Three Old Gods guide you.
Keep an eye on <<1>>. He'd light himself on fire if he got half a chance.
Get me out of these bonds, quickly! If I know her, she'll be halfway to the next village before I catch up!
My wife is being held somewhere. Let's get moving.
The quicker we find a way out of here, the quicker we can rescue Sai. Let's go!
Ah, the brave and mysterious champion returns. Do you have something for me?
What do you want now?
At least I'll get a good scar out of this.

The poison pulls from Jorunn's memories and gives strength to his greatest fears. The death of his sister, the soldiers in his service, and Fildgor.nnHis dreams have created guardians to hide his true memories. You must show him the truth of things.

By the Pact, that was horrible! I could feel his spirit energy draining away!nnI can't believe you chose to sacrifice Raen, but I won't waste his gift. I'll do whatever I can to rescue the Silvenar and help you.
That's a hard decision, friend.nnI'll do what I can in Sariel's memory to help you rescue the Silvenar, lest her screams echo in my ears for eternity.
Tell Selgaard his wife waits for him. I will protect our home until he returns.
I can speak. And you understand me?nnShould I  be thankful for this sentience? The others were nothing but beasts after the change.
My bonds are broken! I'm free of that vermin-infested cave. Now to hunt down more of those damned cultists.
My colleagues killed or wounded, our work destroyed. This affront must be avenged.
My Treva. He came to me, spoke to me. Told me he was free of the Worm Cult's grip.nnThank you. May Kyne watch you on your travels.
target: My Treva. He came to me, spoke to me. Told me he was free del Culto del Verme's grip.nnThank you. May Kyne watch you on your travels.

source: Keep looking. We need to know more before we act!
You're through the barrier, yeah? Why are you wasting time talking to me? Get in there.

I am <<c:1>>, the spiritual advisor to  why, it's you! Wonderful.nnWood Orcs from <<2>> have captured me, and I don't know why. I am loath to impose upon your aid yet again, but I have nowhere else to turn.
We are victorious and the Ebonheart Pact is sealed.nnGo, inform my son that the battle is won. Have him prepare to take Fildgor to prison.
By storm and wind, we shan't let them pass. The future of the Dominion is in our hands.  We will fight until the last one falls!
The Houndsmen and the Drublog, working together to destroy my connection to the land! I can't believe it.nnThankfully, you saved me.
Thank you again. You'll receive a glowing mention in my report on our ill-fated expedition.
Please, help. The Drublog .
For a savage, you show promise. Just a bit, mind you.nnPerhaps one more act will earn you my respect.
What happened up there? I heard fighting!
I'm sure I don't have long to live. Netapatuu tells me my wounds are minor, but I know better. oh, death would be better than this agony!
I knew you'd make it. Thallik lead the cultists into the barrow beyond. Good luck.
Valdur told me of your deeds at Taarengrav. nnNow our heroes have gathered, and we will need all of you to beat these damn Worms and take back what is ours!
You dealt with those boars admirably. I don't suppose you could help me with a bigger problem?
Found any other strange materials for me to blow up?
Many more would grieve by the river today, if not for you. Thank you, my friend.
I never doubted this would happen, but the feeling of relief is overwhelming.nnThe celebrations continue for several days and nights, but the handfast is complete!
I'm glad you're on our side!
I don't know what magic summons the Guardian of Silvenar, but if you go to the bridge, it should appear. Defeat it, then head into the city.
Thank you for helping us.
No, it can't end like this! He promised!
We'll never forget your part in this story.
Celebrations will continue for many, many days.
I don't see my husband anywhere. This doesn't feel right.
The giants have finally calmed down, but I'm not sure I want to move back into Lower Yorgrim.
I can't believe things will end this way! They can't.
The handfast ritual is but one of the many ceremonies for this wedding.nnLook around, my friend. Without you, this joyous celebration could not be possible.
See you later, friend. Perhaps we'll meet again.nnIn fact, I hope we will.
After a tragedy like this, it may be best to abandon this place.
One of our strikers will meet you inside the cave.nnThe captain has an iron will, but I fear she won't hold out much longer, if the tales of <<1>> are true.
Both the Commander and Thod were heading toward the barracks. I'm sure you can catch up with them if you hurry.
Who knew party planning could be so much work! It's enough to drive Rigurt to drink. If only the mead had arrived.
Now that the meadery is back in business, I barely have enough time to eat and sleep.
What indignity! What utter .nnWhat? Who are you? Leave me alone. I'm not doing anything.

The gates have been sealed since we arrived, but Lord Vurlop should be able to open them. nnKing Jorunn was adamant that no one disturb the meeting. I imagine that whatever they are discussing in there, Fildgor is definitely at the heart of it.
Excellent! You are here. And you are all fancy! All cultural and everything.
Arithiel did right by us. If it weren't for her, we wouldn't be alive.
<<1>>  still breathes. See to that.
The Worm Cult! Here?nnI don't have the forces to take down a cabal of necromancers. Is there anything you can do?
The shadow's lifted! For the first time in many moons, my spirit is my own. I can see my destiny again.nnWithout your help, the Silvenar might never have made it back. I hope I didn't injure you.
Yes! Finally! I'm sure the feast will be fantastic!
Why would anyone attack us? We never did anything to deserve this!
Move along.
You bring the magicka. Good luck!
I heard you went through the portal and defeated <<1>>. I can't thank you enough.
I heard you went through the portal and defeated <<1>>. I can't thank you enough.
My people should not suffer for any problems within my court. I should have seen Betar-Nes's treachery before it came to roost in my very hall.
Was that your first encounter with a Daedric Titan? No? You lead a charmed life, I see.
Got a cold greeting, eh? For what it's worth, I'd be glad of any help you give while you're here.
What's the delay?
So, did you find Sadri? Did you get the deed?
We showed Fildgor's minions what for! They won't come back here any time soon.
Bring back the head of the alpha troll to honor my people. Do what your Prince's guards refused to do.nnThen I'll consider speaking with the others again.

"Maybe we should go upstairs so I can protect you." Who even says that? He could have complimented my eyes! Or my  nevermind.nnHe's one of Dhalen's thugs. No sign of the King, though. Not sure if that's a good thing or a bad thing.
Tell Aera I'm headed to Golun's place.nnThen enjoy Nimalten. More importantly, stay out of my damn way.
Hallfrida grew up knowing me as her father's advisor. Still she doesn't trust me. I'll have to fix her mistakes later, as I always have.
The nightmare begins again. You should have left sooner. Now you're trapped here with us, to the bitter end.
Have you learned anything more about the murder?
You can't leave me with this crazy woman. She has that look in her eyes. I don't want to die.
Found the captain, yeah? Ysgramor's strength stands before me.
You will be forever in our prayers.
Voranil lives. For now.nnWe are thankful for your help, stranger, but if I were you I would have fled long ago. The Keepers and I, we must stop Rilisat any cost.
Good day, hero of Mournhold and Deshaan! I hate to interrupt your victory, but I'm here to request your assistance.
Is  is this my silk?
You can't know how grateful I am for this.
Did you find anything?
Thank you for your time and support. May I have the beads back?
<<1>>? I think I felt her! Did you find her?
I'm dry with apprehension, comrade. Everywhere, I smell musty rot.nnIt's so different than the rot of the swamp. It makes my scales itch.
You're not that bad, for an outsider.
This one has not been to a Dwarven ruin in some time. It is not a problem for Aelif. The steam ruins her fur. The noise hurts her ears. nnIt's better that you go, comrade.
I can't wait to see those losers' faces!
There were too many of them. They overpowered me and tossed me in here.
Ah, you've arrived at just the right time. What I'm doing will concern you as much as it concerns me.nnWe're looking at an invasion.
You! You must listen to me!
Companions, workers, find them and save them. Who am I forgetting? Oh, right. Did I mention how grateful my sister Kireth will be to see your face?
Thank you. We can't let the Worm Cult accomplish their goal here. We'll keep these survivors safe until you return.
So. What did the notes say? No rush. Take your time.
I didn't expect this outcome, to be honest. But there, you've done what you set out to do and saved Finoriell.nnGood.
So many sacrifices this day! But look! Finoriell was saved!
Why are you talking to me now? Finoriell's safe! Talk to her!
You and Lara saved me. I would be nothing, forgotten! What would that be like, to be  unmade like that?
What're you hanging around here for? Leave while you can!
Follow Merric's instructions. He's the only one who knows how to make this weapon.
It's been so long. I'm free. And you saved me. Thank you, liege-lord.
You've been a huge help to us. Many thanks.
My head feels like it's going to crack in two. But some things are clearer.
You've learned the tune, yes? Now we can move on to planning the performance.
You should talk to the boss woman. There's no returning to the Earth Forge for you.
We'll figure this out in time. Speak carefully. Let no one hear anything we've planned.
We'll deal with Thorulf later. In the meantime, I know our soldiers can hold the walls. nnStill. Dark Elves defend. Nords attack.
So Shalidor found you. I've been hoping to begin soon. nnThe first book has been translated. Are you prepared for Sheogorath's first test?
I'd just speak to him and get it over with. I don't trust him, but I'm sure he'll do you no harm. You are, after all, his instrument for the moment.
Violence is one of my favorite forms of madness.
I see my porter found you. I'm glad you came. I figured out what the last book was referring to.
You're back? They told you, didn't they? About their plotting? They can't have it. They'll never have it!
She's waiting for you at the Rawl'kha Guildhall in Reaper's March. Good luck, comrade.
Finally on my last round of inventory! Can I help you?
Have you completed the Mad God's trial?
The Champion of Windhelm?nnIt takes more than winning a foot race and play fighting to make a true champion. A silly title. That's all it is.
Nimalten reminds me of Bleakrock. All these good people, oblivious to danger. If only we could have protected my family. nnHave you learned anything?
Leave this place and find <<1>>. I will meet you outside.
So you broke the Reach's lock on the mine entrance, nice. We'll hold them out here if you take them on inside the mine.
Good, the entrance should be unlocked now.
She's preparing a ritual space at the Rawl'kha Guildhall in Reaper's March. I'll see you there, Adept. We're so close!
I'll search for any other survivors who've escaped.
This is the end of the Bridge. Beyond lies Sovngarde, the realm of the honored dead.nnIt is not a place for the living. Turn back.
Through the caves, you will find the grove of insects. If you follow the story's path, you can't miss it.
Don't be fooled by appearances. Trust what the amulet shows you!
Forward! We must reach <<1>>.
<<1>> is a mountain we must surmount. And you must lead us.
There is no time for failure. If you cannot lead us to <<1>>, we must find someone who can.
It was carrying a salmon? I wasn't fishing for salmon. The salmon fishing is done off the docks. That-a-way, beyond the warehouse.
Trolhetta has been a slaughterhouse. So many have fallen.
Go to Eyevea and meet Shalidor. I'll bring the others mages along shortly.
Do what you can for the civilians who crossed the bridge. Remember, they aren't soldiers; they need our help.nnI'll meet you in one of the burnt-out buildings.
You've saved Velyn Harbor from devasation, and the Fists of Thalmor from a great embarrassment.nnSpeaking of great embarrassments, please talk to <<1>>.
I love it when a plan comes together!nnReally, you'd think forest spirits wouldn't be so greedy with their things.
Good choice.
The other traders are in the merchant stalls. For now, all we need is their word.
Soorba will follow you all over Velyn Harbor and fight at your side, but don't leave the area or she'll just come back to me.
It falls to us. We must rally the Companions and face Sinmur together. Are you with me?
Not a moment too soon!nnIt's as I suspected. The village is in considerable danger!
You've witnessed the Master General's testimony. There is no denying Sees-All-Colors' guilt. nnShe murdered <<1>>.

I need you to catch torchbugs. I need five pairs of wings. No more, no less.nnI also need the satchel from my homethe intact building, the one with the sturdy lock. The key should be in an urn near the house. I tossed it in there when I ran by.
Hey there! I'm just preparing some oats for the horses. You need anything, you should talk to Afneer. He'll set you right.
We could use someone like you in the Fighters Guild. If you're interested, speak to the Hall Steward Raki.
Hail, friend. If you want to join the Fighters Guild, talk to Hall Steward Raki.
If you want to join the Fighters Guild, you need to speak to Raki. She's the Hall Steward here.
If you aren't going to deliver what you promised, I have no further use for you.nnGo away. You're spoiling my bath.
Ho there. We've been hearing about your exploits from Veldrana. We're up here looking for a patrol from Riften that seems to have gone missing.
Is my nose still here? I think it may have snapped off.
You return. I am almost afraid to ask, butwhat news?
I prayed for your safe return. It's good to be out under the open sky again.nnI hope  I hope Uricantar went down without much struggle.
Be careful. It seems <<1>> has gone quite mad.
I tried to stop him. I couldn't  I couldn't help them.
Well, yes, I suppose the sergeant is correct. It is an interesting tale  a tale of how I saved my command!nnI don't know why she should think you need to know it, but I'll tell you if you insist.
I  how  you  argh! I can't believe you beat me! No one ever beats me!
Point the bow the other way. Those arrows are dangerous.
They  came from nowhere. By boat, maybe. Never been this far inland. Captain Ciranya .
You have a <<1>>? What are you waiting for? Get in there and destroy the beacon!
It isn't that I'm overly bloodthirsty, you understand, but I can't stomach betrayal. Kill one of those troublesome lieutenants and the other will get the point.nnI'll be here, nursing my wound.

These Maormer are far from home. nnAs a young lad, I heard many a tale of the Pyandonean pirates. I assumed they were apocryphal. Dreamed up to frighten children. I was wrong. They're every bit as bloodthirsty as the stories would have us believe.
The shallows in this bay are treacherous, but the Maormer navigated through those reefs like they've been doing it their whole lives.
<<1>>'s in bad shape, but he'll pull through.
Have you recovered it? Did you rescue Akatosh's claw from those brigands?
I should warn you. Three coins say Norion is down in the crypts.
A moment. I need all my concentration to do this.
The King's Arrow? Well met. Don't suppose you lead a vanguard of troops to Vernim?
You must banish Colonwe's spirit before I can perform the ritual!
The forging of the crystal with the lattice takes an extraordinary amount of discipline.
Let us do it. This outrage has gone on long enough.
Queen's favorite, I'm glad you're here. We came to Tanzelwil to honor the spirits of our ancestors, and now they seem bloody well determined to kill us all!
A mortal willing to right a mortal wrong. Intriguing, but we have been disappointed before.
Speak with my sister.
The rest of the crew's waiting beyond the cave's exit. I'll follow shortly, when I am sure we aren't being followed.nnNow go! Get the captain to safety.
Go on. I look forward to leading my crew far away from this terrible place.
Search the area for more of the stones and destroy them. Ancestral spirits usually don't try to kill their living descendants.
<<1>> brought the shards you'd retrieved into the ruins for the final battle.nnWith only two shards, you have little chance of defeating Sinmur by yourself.
A little busy here. I must keep this shield up.
Please be quick.
My aunt will be so disappointed when she gets the news.
Sorry. No time to talk.
Into the fray with one of the Five Hundred at your side. Make us proud.
Ma'am! Glad I found you. The Silvenar told us to keep eyes out for you.nnWe're kind of in the frying pan here.
I sense it. In the cave, just over there. Go quickly, while I still have control.
The fires are under control, thanks to you.

It has been a long time, hasn't it? I hope you remember Walks-in-Ash, as well? She's out there in the field. Tending to the wounded out there. Forbade me from joining her, said I'm needed here. Damn her scales.
You've found the blade? Excellent.nnPut the ivory in the pit and let the ritual begin.
There you are. It's as I said, the medicine isn't working. It's just holding off the inevitable. Vadda'ra thinks the rest will not survive much longer.
Hurry, the urns that bind me here must be destroyed!nnI'm coming with you. You need all the help you can get.
Best of luck up there. Those ruins are overrun with spirits. Not what I signed up for.
