They've taken my lighthouse. It's the only life I know.
The Green Hunters encoded their plans, and divided its pieces amongst themselves. Search every one you can to get the whole document. I'd do it myself, but I'd leave a bloody trail behind.
I wonder the rest of the squad is still alive
You're a right bastard, you know that? Still  maybe she needed less coddling. Get out of here, and make the Worm Cult pay for what they did to my brother.
That's done it! One less angry werewolf to plague Malabal-Tor!nnMany thanks! The other minstrels have accepted me again, and we're going to practice for the celebrations.
Stop it! Stop laughing! Damn you all, stop laughing!
Grimclaw will never complain about our music again!
I don't know what everyone's so upset about! This is our big opportunity. Yes, we still need practice, but the celebration goes on for days! People will like seeing us get better over time.
Well, Laen may not be a traitor, but she still wants to keep me from singing at the handfast! And look at this harp! Those beasts nearly destroyed it.
Don't take too long with him.
Use the <<1>> on a giant and we'll be able to focus our spell on it. Getting close enough will be the problem. After that, leave the rest to us.
They all died because I was not strong enough. Fjola, Gord, Valgerd  I'm sorry.
This is an unmitigated disaster. What is the Queen thinking?
One day, over a drink, you must tell me what happened down there. For now, the Queen's safety is my primary concern.
It seems no tale ever truly ends. The characters change, but the tale goes on.nnNow, we must fulfill our roles.
Luxuries and delicacies from the far-off land of Elsweyr! What is your pleasure today?
So you found the peak. You'll not live to tell of your discovery!
Nothing like a good, strong drink!
So much of my past is now a scorched ruin.nnIt is yet another reason to hate Molag Bal and his twisted minions.
All that live must die someday. Perhaps this is my day.
Four years. I've been at this party for four years. The Argonian body wasn't meant to take this kind of abuse. But every time I try to leave, someone shoves a bottle at me. And here I stay.
Hanilan, of the First Auridon Marines, at your service.
Defeat <<1>> and we'll scatter the Worm Cult to the four winds.
Do you really think we can kill <<1>>?
Come quickly! They took Honorable Eraral-dro!
Help defeat <<1>>. I'm counting on you!
Is it true? The barrier is down? We're one step closer to reclaiming Firsthold!
I heard the barrier is down. We're one step closer to reclaiming Firsthold!
Razum-dar mentioned he would speak with you. Seek him out and return to the Queen once you're done.
We're back! The High Kinlord is safe and Queen Ayrenn's alliance is secure.nnNot bad for a day's work.
If any of those haughty High Elves don't fancy a drink  well, you may have to be a bit more insistent.
Enjoying the party, fellow Ebonheart Pact citizen?
What do you want?
Oh, hello. You're going to hurt me, aren't you?
The Queen received word of your impressive efforts in Silsailen. You're all she can talk about.
Master Pellingare wouldn't believe me when I told him his son and daughter were plotting to attack this city.nnHe no longer has a choice.
Word is, you've won a few fights. Good work.
Ahh, a true fighter! Well fought.
That was some display. Ysgramor's strength!
Music has its place, though I prefer the spoken word.
I knew this lousy job wasn't over. Must I sling more libations for my captors?
No one moves. They should be dancing.
What's with all the dialog? The people demand music!
Both of us are best served by never mentioning Bar-Neeus's name again.
This one knew you were a winner. That's why this one bet so much money on you!nnTake it as a compliment.
You said you left him bound in the mine, right?
I thank the Stars I found that book on salloweed. Without it, we'd have no defense against this wretched disease.
Please, we're very busy here. Give us some room.
Wha? What are you doing talking to me? Get going!
You've done me a great favor. I sense a change in the wind in Riften, thanks to you.
This is it. Have you found the answer yet? So close. So close.
I don't think we will ever feel safe here again.
She looks hurt, champion. See to her.
Estre dead. Rilis found. Razum-dar couldn't have asked for more. nnEven this one must admit: you do good work. Without you leading the charge, today could have gone very differently.
I hope you can find them. Ayrenn, the Queen. She'll be so worried.
Thanks! Those cultists really got to me. I'll be ready for them next time!
<<1>>. What can I say? She was nuts. All those cultists are. I wanna kill every one of them, in the most painful ways possible. Sounds like a plan, right?
Welcome to Nimalten, traveler. Do you seek the council of our mighty Thane Fjora? Or are you here with Sergeant Aera's contingent?
Well met. Your stride carries you with purpose. Are you part of Sergeant Aera's squad?
The hero of Bal Foyen returns! What news?
What are you doing here, scum?
Did you swoon? I would have swooned.
Well? What are you standing around for? Get moving!
I can't believe you told her.
I know he's doing good work. But Stars do I wish Hendil would give me back my barn.
If you ask me, this plague is sent by Auri-El. Cull out some of these useless layabouts. Make the town more habitable.
All the good hands got themselves sick. So all the repairs fall to me. Just great.
Excellent. I hope this works.
I'm eager to see this plan in action.
I hope Sinien's plan works. Auri-El watch over you.
I should be able to help with the ritual. Damn it.
I hardly know what to do next, with all that's happened in the last few days.
I thought Arkay would come for me today.
How could you? How could you?
Ah, you must be the one everyone is talking about. It's good to see you've returned. I wasn't sure I could keep the Queen detained much longer.
So. It's finally over.
Not bad, not bad. Not that impressive, either.nnIf you really want to prove yourself -
Grab a mug! Get drinking.
You sick? No? Then get out of here.
Hmph. Quite the busybody about town, aren't you?
Please don't disturb us.
Another round of drinks! Another song!nnAha! And I see I have another ardent admirer.
Tell the Canonreeve what this slime has done.
I must concentrate.
Please, just leave me. Don't look at me.
Next time I see Worm Cultists, they're dead!
With the lich dead, we are all needed elsewhere. Keep your teeth sharp, friend.
Ha! You settled their hash, didn't you? You'll always be welcome around our campfires.
Mages, eh? Such strange creatures. But other than a little bit of stiffness in my neck, I'm no worse the wear for being a lawn ornamentation.
You ready for this?
Glad you made it out, Arrow. I'll make sure Dajaheel and Belron go up on the rolls in Mournhold. It's mad to think of all those people. Reduced to ink on parchment.
I suppose <<1>> wasn't as big a fool as I'd thought.
Well? Where's my share of the treasure? We need to head out before the tide turns again.
Is Rilyn dead? nnOh, this is all my fault. My parents forbade me to see him, but I ignored them. I caused their deaths!
Dunmer bastard snuck up on me. Gutted me like a horker. nnGo after him, save Raerana! He'll kill her if she doesn't go with him.
Helping Hendil. No concern for yourself in the face of plague. Admirable. Very admirable.
Heard you managed to get some more of that alchemy goo. Know a few people that will appreciate that.
This plague is a scourge from the mongrels, I just know it. They're nothing but reservoirs of disease and mange.

We sawand heardso much! I can't believe anyone thought she could bring back the Walking City on her own! Or that she thought it was taken to Oblivion.nnEveryone knows the city rests beneath the great sea until its time to rise!
Looks like you've done some good work here.
Where's <<1>>? Don't tell me you left her at the dragonshrine!
Let's go!
Sure glad you showed up. Those cultists are nasty customers.
I have to keep my eye on the portal. They're depending on me.
Excellent work! They had it coming.
Don't think you can dissuade me. My mind is made up!
Get going. Heldil can't hold him long.
Now that you're here, I'll ask you to check in with the Watch Captain. We're sending all newcomers to speak with her. Astanya's on the docks. Southeast end of the city.
Right. Now that you've passed this along, I'll need to ask you to make for the docks. As a newcomer to the city, the Watch Captain will want to note your arrival.
What happens in the mine? This waiting wears on me.
I do hope she hasn't lost sight of her duties. That woman is too easily flustered.
Keep moving.
The Daggers. They're here. They followed us home!
The days and nights all blur together now.
The Prophet's enclosure isn't far. Let's go!
All of Auridon knows the Veiled Queen is a traitorbut a Daedra worshiper, as well! A High Elf in league with Dagon himself.
I've seen better.
Can't you see we're in the middle of a battle, stranger?
Seek out the Cultist Summoner atop the dais. The evil flows from there.
I'm sorry, I can't help you right now. I'm very busy and there's a lot to do.
Good work, citizen. Glad the captain sent you our way.
What did you find?
Now to look to larger things. I must cement my position, and continue my tour of the isle.
This is it. Last one! What do you say, going to try to puzzle it out yourself?
You're awake now, sleeping kitten?
You saved <<1>> and <<2>> itself. You have our eternal gratitude, my friend.
Well. At least Tanamo is back. Good, reliable Tanamo.nnWhere are the rest of them?
This one can't afford to be caught unprepared. <<1>> will train. Until the Maormer are no longer a source of fear.
I feel terrible. And how is it I'm the one that's managed to show up? Lorkhan's luck.
Not now I must concentrate
I never should have left. Nothing like good solid ground.
Did you find <<1>>?
With you taking care of Varnedo, I can relax a bit. nnMight see if those Nords really know how to drink.
Discover anything new?
You have questions, new friend?
So, everything work out all right?
I'm resting up. Talk to me another time.
<A small pouch sits inside the hollow tree>
You. You're not with them? Quickly, get me out of here!
Remember. No is not an acceptable answer.
Quickly, take the side tunnel to return to the entrance!
You've returned! I thank you again for your help.nnTwo-Blades would like to speak with you.
You arrived just in time.
Be wary, traveler. This corruption could take you, too!
Find my father, outsider. And the rest of the villagers, too.
This one has no time for talk now. I must tend to this poor man. Though I fear with the reagents I have on hand there may be little more I can do.
Hope it's going well for you.
Oh, dear! Did my champion lose his nerve? Please, you must stop Cracktooth!
Well, from the time you've spent in there, I think we may be onto something.
How goes the stealing of the blades? Don't let me down.
Clever, using the back exit. You might have a future with us. How'd it go in there?
Greetings. What can I do for you?
Oh, I hope they are safe.
Did you find my boy, Ulfslod?
They're stocking something in the hut off to the west. Might be worth checking out.
Lodorr's Crown isn't here.
Woo-hoo!
I need another drink. Let's find my friends and get out of this accursed place.
I see you've found one of my friends. Good to know they haven't all been eaten.
You should have seen the fish I almost caught. It was a small whale.
You have the pleasure of speaking with High Kinlady Estre, scion of royal Aldmeri blood. I must apologize, but my escort and I were just in the middle of a conversation. If you'll excuse us?
Bit busy here, if you don't mind?
Welcome to Vulkhel Guard!
A very fitting look for you.
Interesting, so I see Mom's got you on a job. I hope it goes well.
I saw those three drunkards stumble out of here. I assume you had something to do with that. Should have left them to the Draugr if you ask me. nnBut I guess you didn't ask me, did you?
That's the end of the coven, but we still need to get out of here.
Could it be I made the wrong choice?
Eranamo was a good mer. He only wanted to do what he thought was right in his heart.
Right. Now we can go find my sister.
My daughter doesn't deserve this fate!
The voice could've lied about everything. But if I don't try, we'll both be cursed.nnShe's in such a daze. I'd hate for her to know what's happening right now.
It's great to meet you at the gate again. Just like the last time!
Estre must pay for this.
Ah, good. Raz was beginning to worry about you.
Zaban. What happened here, damn it?
Have you finished your tour yet? Make sure to have a run at some of the students. Can't have you telling the Queen we're slacking.
I see you survived. The Ra Gada sure are mad  well done!nnI still haven't recovered enough to cast the disguise ritual on myself, but there's more to be done, anyway.
Sorry. Can't talk.

Those Redguard shouldn't be here. Drinking my booze, stirring up trouble. Sure, we don't always get along with the Wood Elves that well, but what they're doing ain't right.nnGet my booze back and everything'll be fine, though.
Bravely done.
Let's show these Bloodthorn cultists what for!
What I am going to do with that fool Orc. He'll never make it in the Lion Guard.

Two altars broken and still I can sense the Canonreeve's magic. There must be one remaining. Find it and you may find <<1>>.nnBe wary if you doher power has grown immensely if these altars are any indication.
There are two loyal soldiers and one traitor out there. I need you to sort them out!
Hurry it up, will you?
You're freeing us? Are you going to free me, too?
I may have exaggerated a bit. My apologies.
Hurry, please. They could be back any minute!
Greetings. Did Baham send you to this one?
I'm sorry. I have to get back to practice.
I'm sorry. I have to get back to practice.
I'm sorry. I have to get back to practice.
That went better than expected. Now, just do your part .

My friend, you are unbelievably quick! <<1>> hopes the ladies don't also say this to you as well, eh?nnBut no matter you have bested the hourglass, and so you may choose a treasure from my private collection. Congratulations.
Students always complain about our difficult curriculum.nnOf course it's difficult! This is Shad Astula, not the Mages Guild.
Just don't snort the cinnamon. That's bad for you.
Don't stand here with your mouth open. Go!
Reinforcements are on the way. Move. We need that thing up.
I can't believe this is happening to me.
You've come to test your mind? Learn if you have what it takes?
It's only a matter of time before we take the fight to Daggerfall, mark my words.
Thank you. One day, perhaps Ilara's dreams will return. Return to normal.
I'm impressed  and relieved. Memories in this part of the Silvenar's mind tend to be unpleasant at best, deadly at worst. You've proven yourself his true friend.nnI'll help you.
Good work. You're tougher than you look.
Why did you come here? Velian will kill you.
I've dosed Len with enough healing potion so that he'll sleep for hours. Once he's feeling better, these rogues better be gone.nnOtherwise, he'll just try to fight them again.
Congratulations, you beat up some weaklings.
Well. You've got some backbone. Good for you.

Those Bloodthorn cultists ran out of the village like a dragon was chasing them! Glad we had our weapons ready. We cut them down without breaking a sweat.nnDame Clarique wants to know what happened in there when you get a chance.
They'll get what's coming to them, one way or another.
You better get moving. Lyris may need your help.nnI'm going to stay here and make sure the Daedra don't get through.
I'm very grateful for your help. I wanted to help these people, but I couldn't have done it without you.
Here we are. The very embodiment of the Green Lady can be see in this ancient tree.
Fair day! I've been given instructions. Razum-dar needs to speak with you, at once.
Oh Divines, they're going to torture us horribly for that one. But it's worth it just to stick in their craw. Ha!
How do you like that, you Daedra bastards? That felt good.
Damned Daedra. I was a slave in life, and now a slave in death. I'll make them pay for this!
Ah, Lyris. Bit of an idealist, that one. Says she's determined to save us all from eternal torment. Heart's in the right place, I suppose, but the girl's as mad as Sheogorath's jammies.
The captain sent you? Thank Mara.

By the blessings of Tava! Fine work, my friend. nnI have no love of Imperials, but I rejoice in their custom of hoarding weapons. Still, I would not wish this fate on anyone, even my enemies. The Planemeld is far from an instrument of mercy.
I hope we're in time.
Take another look into the rooms before you head down into the library. If there are illusion spells, you'll need every edge you can get.
Were you able to find some petals from Kyne's Tears? They are so hard to find.

As I feared, we arrived in different locations. I am in a place with the smell of burning ash on a hot wind and the sounds of a distant battle. nnIt matters not. You have awakened once again and we must set you on your path.
Find the leader of the side you have chosen and present yourself. I'm eager to see how the game plays out with you involved.
Did you speak to Nelhilda? Smart lass, my daughter. Very smart.

If you're looking for work, there's better to be had elsewhere. The forge is suited for the lesser races, particularly those cats. nnAlmost hate to see the Bosmer work the forge. Mer should stick by mer.
Once I destroy the wards, we can get inside the vault. No problems after that. I'm sure!
Sithis blind me! Be there other living mortals in this wretched waste? You're the first swab I've seen who still has meat on their bones.
Thanks for the bait. Maybe them fish will start biting now.
I wouldn't go into town if I were you. Just keep on to Firsthold.
I hope he's all right.
Me crew is dead. Looks like we be the only living things left in this wretched place.
If you keep the Admiral distracted, I'll convince his crew to join with me  er  us. Without a crew, a captain is powerless.nnExcept for me, of course.
The Amulet is secure, sir.
I wonder how much that Amulet is worth on its own, without the whole magic bit.nnWhat? Idle thoughts, don't look at me like that.
These Daedra deal most generously in the currency of pain.
The face is still good, yeah? Good.
Excuse me, please. I must look for her ring. Can't leave without it.
You're a stubborn one, mate, I'll give you that.
I know a few of the House Hlaalu guards. I heard how you helped them find a cure for the plague.
Enter the portal and find the source of the power I sense emanating from the other side.
Please find my husband! His name is Pirtar. He was still in the house when the roof fell in!
The attack was so sudden. We barely made it out alive.
The Daedra. Everywhere. Damn those things are fast.
Thank the Eight! Please tell me the Marines have arrived.
Thank the Divines I found you. nnYou need to find Landare. She's in over her head.
I feel my strength returning. I should be as good as new in a few days.
The guards are quiet again. Something's happened.nnWhere's my son? Where's Sorondil?

Bernt gave my lute back. It feels right to have it in my hands again.nnI showed great promise when I was young and Bernt had it made for me. Sent all the way from Windhelm and made by the finest lute crafter in the land.
Why is  why is Angof helping me?nnWhat  what's going on here?
Are you mad? You decided to help Thallik? Willingly? How can you imagine that was a good idea?nnThis one hopes you know what you're doing.
Look at me! I'm a flaming nix!
<Raynor Vanos is sound asleep.>
I had friends and allies once. Companions who would never abandon me, no matter the cost. But that was before. Before I became this  monster.nnEnough! I must find the magic to restore my human form.
Hey there. Ever spend any time staring at your own corpse?nnI don't recommend it.
<Lady Laurent doesn't seem to hear you.>
Off with you. Off!nnSpill blood. Stab things. Do what you do best!
The shadow wanted my help, but I never asked what it wanted me to do. I  I just gave up.nnIf you can find the shadow, maybe we'll have a chance. I  I just don't know.
Defeat the champions of Angof and Thallik. Then we can have a proper celebration!nnAnd remember, should you need assistance, use my mask of shadows. I think you'll enjoy what happens after that.
I hope you're not here to kill Goblins. If you are, we'll have a problem.
You did it! You've returned my crewmates! My friends.
I hope that our warriors are strong enough to aid you in the coming battle.
You are interfering. The fate of the old tavern keeper and his patrons is none of your concern.
It's been years since I spilled blood in the field. Ah, the memories.
You look to be young and able. Please say you'll help.nnThe Nurin farm has been burned down and Mister Nurin has disappeared. It's very serious.
I feel sorry for Rosalie, but there's nothing more these old bones can do.nnI only stayed on the farm these last few years for William's sake, and I hate to say it, but I think he died in the fire.
I failed.
If I lose my pack beasts and all my money, I'm doomed. I might as well die here.
Your valiant rescue of the First Auridon Marines was well-timed. They've driven off the last of the imposters.nnWhat news of the traitor, Teldur? Was Canonreeve Valano injured?
Masterful! Did you take dance lessons, or are you naturally graceful?nnI suppose I shouldn't tease. You did much better than I would have. I'm sure <<1>> will appreciate your hard work.
Return once you've convinced Drulis to do his job. If he won't, perhaps you'd undertake it.
We just need to hold a little longer.
I knew Nelhilda would hate me for this.nnI almost said I would give anything for her forgiveness, but I've learned the dangers of making wishes.
The observatory is just below us.
We'll keep the pirates off your tail, I swear it!
They attacked the lighthouse? But why? That doesn't make any sense.nnCan I see these plans?
You're a clever one. I figured this would all end in bloodshed. Turning an Orc's wounded pride against him is no easy task.
We'll distract the pirates while you slip into the Fighters Guild.nnHurry, before they can arm their undead with every weapon in that building.
Please, don't let her take me back! I'll give back the trinkets, but I can't go back!
She's my property, as surely as that locket is. But if you're determined to free her, there's nothing I can do about it. You're the one who's armed here, after all.
We must stop the Daedra before they can steal the Amulet!
Is it done? Is <<1>> dead?
Ask questions later. You need to get spriggan bark so we can save your remaining friend.
Ifriz isn't in the Fighters Guild? I don't understand how I could have been so mistaken.

Watch out for Captain Angarthalhis axes are stained with the blood of more sailors than I can count. He's a monster. nnHey though. If you're feeling tough, I say take that bastard out. Won't hear any complaints from me.
It's all my fault. We wouldn't be out here if it weren't for me.
He left a note? I don't know how to mix the ingredients!nnMaybe you can figure it out his word-play. There must be something in the way he described the ingredients. Take a look at his note again.
Don't dawdle with me, get the Amulet!
The Amulet is safe, but it looks like whatever it did drained its power.
I have nothing to say to you.
Oh, hello. Guess I should've expected to see you around. Not that it isn't good to see you, but .nnWhy are you here, exactly?
Why would you say that about my mother?  You don't even know her!  You can pass the "Or Step" test case  jerk.
We have nothing to discuss. I'll meet you below.
Sai Sahan is one of the greatest warriors of the age. He shall be a powerful ally in battle.
What happened? Why did <<1>> sound so strange?
Sorry, but Master Tuunerol is currently away. I can't grant you access without his express permission.
The race is on!

It's  surprising to get help from a stranger out here. Thank you.nnThree journals should be enough. Knowing the whoreson dogs that live out hereI mean that literallyI'm assuming at least one was eaten or defecated on.
Uh, can I help you? Very busy here.
Can I help you? Just watching the races. Noting that Snooks is a superior specimen in almost every way.
What do you want? Look at you, weakling. Even my frog could rip you apart.
It should be easy to grab those baubles and get back before anyone's the wiser.
A mother shouldn't outlive her children. And I've had four pass on to Aetherius. It's almost too much to bear.
Vox is defeated, order is restored. You are a credit to your people.
Use the list to track them down. Good luck, and show no mercy.
Why would you say that about my mother?  You don't even know her!  You can pass the "Or Step" test case  jerk.
<<1>> is a lovestruck fool. At least she didn't get anyone killed.
What is it now?
Bandits rushed the gates and scaled the walls. There's not enough of us to drive them back!
A fellow seeker of knowledge! I can tell by the glint in your eye. <<AC:1>> is a marvelous find, is it not?
You don't fool me! It looks like you're helping us, but I know you must be up to something.nnJust remember that I'm keeping my eye on you.
Statues with living eyes. They were always watching! And the bones .
Ah, my arms! I thought they were going to fall off.nnI'm glad the eyeball was worth it. So good when a theory works in practice, you know?
Ah! Stay back, pirate!
Who are these Pact-soldiers? Are they merciful new friend's allies? <<1>> hopes they come to stop <<2>>!
We're under attack!
Well, did you add our special ingredient to the Imperials' food?
Ready?
Hello, murderous. We both expect to see you at the estate. nnYou don't want to disappoint us, do you?
As mud is my mother, what is the Canonreeve planning?nnThe air is tinged with an aura of magic I've never felt before.
What an obscure ritual. I've never seen its like. Seems Bakkhara was right, and the Canonreeve is no mere politician.nnPerhaps I wasn't wasted on this mission after all.
You need something. I can tell.
Ah, the little meddler. Enjoying yourself so far? You're like a Dwemer toy that doesn't need to be wound up. You do all the work yourself and I just watch and smile.

Welcome to Sentinel, grunt. I wish I could have gotten some of that action on the docks. But, you knowpolitics. nnTake a moment to look around. We've got all the tools of the trade. Point one out and we'll make a deal.
Be quiet! That thing might hear! We can speak after it's gone.
Now that Vox no longer threatens us, I'm sure things will return to normal.
Tell me, was the entrance to the crypt breached?
Thank you for helping search for my family's remains.
As you see, Headman Bhosek's trust in my skills was not misplaced. Nor was my faith in your prowess.nnWill you assist me on another task?
The traitors lost their fight once you killed <<1>>. I'd rather hang the lot of them, but <<2>> said some were coerced into it.nnEven so, they'll need some kind of punishment.
Yes? Is it done?
Auri-El watch your steps. I'm very excited about this project. Shalidor's sanctuary would be a boon to every mage in Tamriel. Even Guildmaster Vanus approves of our work here!
If there's anything consistent about Sheogorath, it's his knack for surprises. nnCome. Let's return to Valaste now that you've recovered the second book.
Are you still on the first act? Very good. A true professional always prolongs the first act.

I hope that goblin chief understands your generosity in sparing him. We'll take charge from here. With any luck, we can relocate Koth and his tribe.nnAnd thank you for dealing with Nelanya so I wouldn't have to. I've found quite the boon in you.
The mutiny's over? He's dead?nnOh, it's done! I think I need to sit down.
How did it go, dearie? The faithful have been served at Baan Dar's bar, yes?
Be on guard if you're headed up to the castle. King Fahara'jhad's army is camped outside the walls.nnThey claim they're here in a diplomatic capacity, but I'm not buying it.
Listen to this braggart. Claims he could drop us all with a hand behind his back. The nerve.nnAnd King Fahara'jad claims these warriors are here in a diplomatic capacity? Preposterous!
Byz not get in way! Let Byz alone!
So you haven't been briefed? News travels slower than honeymead in the field.
Good, you have arrived.
Are you expecting me to fetch it for you? I'm no servant of yours, mortal.
You! You're the one who rescued me from those slavers in Koeglin. nnI can't thank you enough. They would have killed me for certain.
What you want? Go away!
Shazah and I rarely agree on anything. But your role in the Dance  this could be important. Not important like the monks and their books. Actually important.
You're not changing your mind, are you? Please don't!
You look like you know something of my father. Tell me.
If it isn't too much trouble, would you bring me the skulls of the Imperial mages? It will allow me to stop the ritual that sustains me in this terrible fashion.
Shazah wasn't sure to believe you  couldn't believe you. But it is true. You are the Moon Hallowed!
This is very exciting!
My "husband," Quintus Verres, is around here somewhere. He's got every scrap of research I've done on these ruins and the Guardian's Eye. I need my materials back.
If you are wounded, you may take a bed in the corner. I will tend to you as soon as I can.
Can you get the sword for me? I'll prepare the stinking flesh needed to lure out the beast. It's Mother's special recipe.
You're back. Good. Do you know what this cult is planning?
Ugh. My head thanks you for your haste. Once the barrier fell, whatever she was doing stopped as well!
It was horrible. They descended like wolves.nnIf Dark hadn't been with me, I don't want to imagine what they might have done.
I am to protect Eling at any cost. I did not fail. nnThe bandits made off with some of our goods, but Eling is uninjured. That is what is important.
You aren't a cultist, are you? Please. Help me! They took me from my tribe!
Hello to you, Aniel's friend. This one wishes we had brought more moon-sugar with us. Roasts always taste better lathered in sweet.
I'm not proud of what we've decided to do, but we might as well get it over with.
A bit rusty, but not bad! So funny, watching you mortals muck around with things you can't possibly understand.nnI'll be needing that back, now.
As I expected. <<1>> is hiding something, but I don't know what.nnGood thing we've already planned for this. Are you ready for a little subterfuge?
Can't wait to see the look on <<1>>'s face when I prank her this year.nnHello there, stranger! Having fun at the festival?
You have the <<1>>? This is going to be amazing!
Quick, follow him! Don't lose the courier!nnYou've got to be the first person to find him when the poison takes hold. I'll meet you at the farm.
Good. You made it! Thank you for rallying these brave men and women. We stand a chance now!
You don't belong here.
Remember, get arms caches and bring to Khajiit out by the shoreline. He will have your money waiting for you.
Shame about Captain Helane. I hear even a touch of that poison gives you the runs for years, though. That'll keep me grinning.

The sergeant said Velyn Harbor would have fallen without you. Honor to meet youI'm the Green Lady. The, uh, the new one.nnI could use your help. The Drublog clan usually side with my people in times of war. We need to learn what changed.
Have you spoken to my father? We must hurry, with or without his blessing.
<<1>> told me she'd wait for the right champion at the upper arena's gates.nnGo and do what you must.
I'm surprised House Dres managed to do anything with the Ordinators on high alert. Not much gets past them, even when they're not looking for trouble.
Did you get it? I'm going to need that wine if this ruse is going to work.
Impressive.
I watched you fight. Impressive.
Soon. Soon you too will know of my greatness.
Tell Daljari you bested some brawlers. Then come back here so I can knock you around.
Once again, you return safely from the dream, bringing one of Vaermina's victims back with you.nnGeneral Godrun seems to be feeling himself again.
Your technique is good but that is rarely good enough.
Bthzark is on the north side of the island. Neramo should be poking around the ruins.
Tell Daljari you're ready for a real fight.
I didn't expect to get help so quickly. Remind me to thank Kaleen when we're done here.
Where do you think I found my husband? Hiding! Hiding in a tree stump!
I'm going to stick around and see what I can salvage here. Pity about poor Raston, though.
Follow the rules. Talk to Daljari and then we can fight.
You should give the bucket to Jill.
What do you want?
Follow the road to the mine. I'll be right there.
You desecrate a few old graves, and already the Bretons are back to complain.nnNice work dealing with the cult. Warchief Tazgol will be pleased.
If the Maulborn figured out a way to reactivate these wards, they have more powerful allies than we thought. nnNow be careful and get your shapely butt moving.
My friend! As you can see, my lovely wife Liane found me. I mean, I found her! We found each other!nnPlease give me good news. Please.
Let me do the talking, won't you?
These are troubled times in Stormhaven. nnI should be focused on the Daggerfall Covenant as a whole, but it would be unwise to neglect the threats to our home lest we lose that which we fight for.
I'll have this guillotine down and burned before the day's over. You have my word.
Please  you have to help. They're trapped. There's no help coming, and they don't know it.
Get out of my house! Put on a shirt and get back to the arena, whelp!
Thank you for helping <<1>> find me.
Thank you for sparing my cousin. nnEspecially since I'm sure he doesn't deserve it. The old rascal.
I'll be sure to credit you when I present my findings to the Mages Guild. Thank you again!
Hurry! If the guards catch you, they'll have your head on a pike!
I hope you made the right choice. It is done. Other matters concern us now.
We've got a crew to rival the legends! Time to make some money, don't you agree?
I am done talking. Make the right decision!
Now, put it over your head and get out of my sight.
Well, look who's come to pay a visit!
The man is a pig. But then, aren't they all?
By the Empyrean Light. The Worm Cult brought his spirit back, didn't they? And you led him here.

I feel  free. It's as though a burden has been lifted from me, a burden I didn't know I carried.nnWhatever you did, it feels  right. When my memory returns, I'll find you and thank you properly for this.
Another day, another whipping. This job just gets better and better.
Endarwe has to know more. Talk to him again.
Shuzura knows how I feel about her. Just make sure to rub it in. Heh.
Khali  damn it. So strong, so forceful. So stupid when it comes to things like this. nnI suppose there's nothing else for it. We have to make for Dune.
You're a gift from the Stars. Once you're into the tunnels, Telenger should be easy to find. Do whatever it takes to get that old fool out of there.
Shazah  damn it. Why did she force me into this? nnI suppose there's nothing else for it. We have to make for Dune.
I should warn you, Gloo is a little  odd. But she's a damned genius when it comes to alchemy.
Good timing. We need to get some information out of our friend here. She seems pretty dense.nnI was just telling her how delicious I find silent tongues.
You're going to do great! Just, whatever you do, don't  err. nnYou know what? I forget. Probably wasn't important. Meet me at my workshop, northwest edge of the village, when you're done.
I wanted to pick up something nice for Captain Kaleen. Something to surprise her, like a new mug. But all this stuff is so expensive!
If the Countess is truly sick, I am more than a little bit concerned. nnI would not wish to remain in this village if she was not in charge.
We have sailed often to Betnikh these last years. Chief Tazgol is a gracious host. In many ways, this is my second home.
If it's true that the Countess is well, no longer able to manage her estate I hope it's Sir Brice who takes over.
A hive of ants is no less busy  or determined  than our captain. I am honored to serve upon this ship.
Don't let me die in here!
You journey into danger. Choose your steps carefully.
Bah, the dull claws on you. Do you have any idea how many coins you're leaving on the table?
Thank you. You have made a wise decision. The Bright Moons will sing your name for this.
Kalari will be all right, you will see. Just needs some time to deal with what has happened.nnGo, speak to Shuzura. She will want to hear from you.
You haven't finished serving everyone at the bar yet!
He came stalking back here, mad as a wet Khajiit. You'd better talk to him.
You smell like burnt corn. Is it done?
My, my. So the Arbordawn cult has been spun into Mephala's web. Fascinating. Worrying, to be sure! But fascinating.
Fivefold venerations upon you, traveler. What brings you to the Falinesti Autumn site?
Welcome to the Falinesti Autumn site. I'm with the team Telenger has brought. What brings you this way?
Welcome to the Falinesti Autumn site. Ghadar is working with the famed Artificer Telenger to study the site.
Don't worry. Tazia will not be moving. She has no interest in any kind of heroics.

That mapit marks the location of our treasures! Listen, I don't know how you got it, and I can't stop you from looking for those relics with these necromancers around, but if you find them, bring them to me.nnI'll make it worth your while.
Did you do it? Did you kill the Goblin king?
There's more to this plot than simply spreading chaos across the land. I won't rest until we uncover the truth behind this assassination attempt.
This is it! Either we break them or they break us!nnWhere is everyone? It's going to take more than just me!
Well? What did you find? Did he leave behind some papers, something to show what's going on in Shuzura's town?
I know we have just met, but you must listen to me. You must decide, do your duty. Destroy the circlet.
What are you still doing here? Shuzura will be wanting you there now, not when you feel like it.
Still waiting to hear why I need you.
You again? What's it this time?
Keep your eyes peeled. This place is crawling with surprises.
Hey there! You look like you don't have anything to do. The guy over there seems to be in dire need of help.
Why are you still here? Go away.
I honor you for bringing news of my brother's death. Now I know his fate, sad as it was.
Ha! I didn't think I'd ever find you. You move around.
What were you doing in the mine? And did you see a scummy Breton up there?
I'll take the Baron back to town with me. The magistrate will know what to do with him.
Ah! Thank Alkosh you found her! We've lost enough soldiers today without adding our best scout to their ranks. nnWith luck, the two of you will find more, yes?
What a day.
If you choose to destroy the relic, then you've turned your back on me and the Covenant. Make the right choice.
Did it go well? Do you have the samples?
Raz could not help but overhear. It is a terrible thing, to tell a person her father is gone.
He's badly hurt. I'll see if I can get him bandaged up.
Head to Moriseli, the Ayleid ruin to the north. Shaman Azlakha is already out there, and she may need help.
Chief Tazgol took the army to Carzog's Demise. Hurry if you want to actually kill any cultists.
I blacked out for a second, thought I died. Did you find the plant sap?

To think that my brother was afflicted by something similar to Sir Hughes  that's frightening indeed. nnI thank you for helping him. I still hope we're able to bring Sir Hughes to justice for what happened to my sweet Lakana.
What're you waiting for? Let's get rid of that pest!
I can't make Goblin's Delight without sugar leaf. Get it and I'll make you a treat you will never forget. Zich loves it!
You! How much more blood do you want?
Spare your blade, Orc. We have yielded to you.
Looks like you found his family. Maybe he isn't as full of Elf dung as I thought.
It's time. The people of Crosswych have taken up arms and are ready to retake their town.nnBut first, <<1>> must die.
We need this shore cleared to advance. Get these lamias off my beach!
My mistake cost my family their home and my people their lives. In my anguish, I sought to redeem myself.
I had my unit scale the sheer cliff behind us, and there was much complaining. The young are weak.nnYou, however, handled that Conduit Stone very well.
So the duchess got killed by one of those high-and-mighty knights?nnFolks like me, we liked herand now she's gone. I hope those knights get what's coming to them.
The ritual tore the veil between Nirn and Oblivion, allowing Mannimarco to begin stealing the souls his master needed to power the Dark Anchors and initiate the Planemeld.
The holy waters of Do'Krin have kept the Claw safe for years. I pray they keep you safe as well.
Why did you invade our island? We had no quarrel with you!
The thought of the dead walking around is unsettling at best. Soon they'll be shambling into Cropsford!
As soon as I know there's nothing in here, we can go. I have a feeling though. Keep looking around.
The spirits have vanished! Their valiant souls rest once again. Quickly tell me what you found below
I need to get these goods shipped to Daggerfall right away. So please, just leave me alone. nnNo offense, but our business is finished and I want nothing more to do with you.
Yes?
Lord Diel is a miserable piece of work. I just hope my brother knows what he's doing.
I've got no love for the Covenant, but it is good to see a few more Orc faces in town.
I think the constable did the right thing. There's something shady about that knight. I've been watching her.

Indaenir's a real piece of work, isn't he? I always thought he was half-mad. They say he has "the Green" in his blood, but most things that man does, I just don't understand. nnRecently though, I've realized just how fortunate we are to have him.

The incessant clamor of the undead at the gate finally stops, and you come through the gateit is a relief to finally see someone new from among the living.nnIs Akkhuz-ri correct in thinking you have come to our aid?
Glad that's done. The pleading of the condemned is almost too much to bear. One way or another, they are returned to the Forest.
That's what the Orcs want, a fight? We could have resolved this hours ago! Though I suppose the captain's not too keen on killing our new friends.
I'm just going to assume at this point that S'rashi's giving me a break. True or not, that's what I'm going with. nnMeans I can head back to the ship . Well, maybe just one more drink first.
Go on, the guards are always good to give a sound beating.
That was unexpected.
First time an outsider's ever beaten me.
That banner has no place in Vlastarus. You know what you need to do.
You have taken many steps along the Path already, Hallowed. Jone and Jode have shown me  just a few more to go.
You made it! I wasn't sure if you would. I haven't had a drink in days, but if you've got the ingredients I need, it's time to celebrate!
Why isn't  why isn't he breathing? nnOh gods, we're too late.
The fighting sounded rather brutal from down here.  You're still in one piece though, so I'll take that as a good sign.
This guar gives its life so we may have meat. Now, I give you my time. Why?
When I leave this place, I will need all my strength. I thank you for my life.
Did you get my lute from <<1>>?
Stretch your tail here in peace.nnWhat brings you to the Hatching Pools?
Been to Crosswych, eh? We'll have the Red Rooks on the run soon enough.
What took you so long?
I'd never seen Sai's proving grounds before. It must have been a serene place before the attack.
I suspect that Vardan died when the portal closed. The body cannot survive without the soul.
You have a container, good. Are you ready for what's next?
This place is pretty impressive.
I need you to listen to me.
This thing must be destroyed!
Don't mind Marius. He was ordered here to look after the interests of the Empire. But really, all he cares for is his own advancement.
Quickly, Hallowed. Close the portal! Sealing it should draw the beasts back to Oblivion.
More wounded arrive by the hour. I hope you have good news for me.
Use the visions as guides, not shackles. Your fate is yours to determine.
Hmph. You've impressed even me. The Dominion owes you yet another debt.
Leave me alone.

You're looking for Sir Hughes, aren't you? Get in line. We've been waiting for him to come and clarify our orders for days. nnHe returned all right. But mumbling incoherently. Know what that means? Just more confusion. I think Hughes has lost it.
I wonder what's taking Jakarn so long? I wouldn't keep a girl like me waiting.
Curse Jakarn! How does he slip about so easily? I turn my back for one moment and he's gone.nnHe's probably off with those slatterns from Stros M'Kai. If I find any of them, it won't be pretty.
You have no idea how long I've waited to taste a good Orcish brew! That swill the Redguards call beer has less kick than a mudcrab.nnNow, if only Lambur would join me.
At last, I find myself looking forward to my future.
The Bright Moons smile down upon us, traveler. The Claw is safe.
You have returned! Bright Moons be praised! Do you  do you have the relics?
I respect the captain, but I won't set foot on an island full of Orcs.
Well, I'm considering waiting til we get out to sea, then throwing you over. I can barely stand the sight of you.

I lost my best daggers when the Maiden's Breath ran aground. I'm going to pick up something new, but the question is what?nnDo I need a new dagger or a trusty mace? Depends on what we're killing, I suppose.
I don't trust these Orcs. Their chief refuses to join the Covenant. No idea why.
I'm  I'm the Mane! Hallowed, we survived!
Hallowed, thank you for dispatching that treacherous Urcelmo. I  have to admit, I'm going to make jokes at his expense for years off this.
Sholg says you talked Lokra out of her wild ideas. You honor our clan. She will be an asset to her people.
Point me at what you'd like slain.
What is it? You want me to stab something?

We've been through quite a bit together, haven't we?nnIf you ever pass this way again, feel free to stop by and visit. I can think of a few other rituals that you can help me with, if you're interested.
Hunal's commentary on your progress has been  most interesting, Hallowed. I hope seeing me alive and well is not too distressing.
I'm sorry, Hallowed. The words of the Moon Bishop have affected me greatly. The thought of my people gone feral, my Silvenar dead .
Hunal tells me you've already progressed well along the path. You continue to impress me, Hallowed.
ON the agony! The affront to our faith and our people!
They have some interesting brews here, don't you think?
The Covenant moved in when they took Drakelowe. As long as they don't make me work, we'll get along.
Too close! They nearly had us that time. The wards will keep the Daedra bound, for now, but I'm still not sure how they managed to break them. We need to investigate Ilmyris.
You have my gratitude. That is no small thing. Zadala always remembers her debts.
The Woodland Man is not wood or land or a man.
Orthenir's soul seals the binding, but without a caretaker the Daedra flee. It is temporary. The mountain is worn away and the tides rise and fall with the same inevitability.
We can get to the Imperial underground through an old guardtower. Raz thinks it's  to the southwest? Yes. Let's go!
Quick work. Word spreads that I have a new collector. I've already gotten back some of the coin I was owed.
What are you doing standing around here? You have your mission. Do not miss the meeting!
Well done. You've made quite a name for yourself among the Shadowscales. nnSoon, our services will be required elsewhere. We may need you again in the future.
Don't bother coming back here until you've run off the Orcs. I've got important business to attend to. Heh.
Hurry! Head into the tunnel and find our leader. She'll explain the plan to you.
It is time for you to go. Leave my body here, where it cannot be bothered again.nnYou have done more than I could have hoped for. Thank you.
Ahh, a traveler. Coming from Dune, sent by the Moon Bishop, if she had to guess. This one is pleased to see you.
My scales are falling out.
This way, it isn't far!
What a day.
The Stormfist thugs captured me. I'm done for!
Beginner's luck. You still need to win three duels.
If the plague of necromancy has truly returned, I fear the future may bring many dark days.nnSomeone will need to come forward to fight the risen dead.
So there you have it. My true form revealed.
Ha! You should've seen Garnikh's face when you won that duel!
Oh, no.nnCheck his body. There must be something to tell us who did this.
Good fight. Garnikh's bitten off more than he can chew this time.
So, I'm next?
Good Thane Harvald here has let me in on your recent accomplishments.nnYou certainly are disrupting Fildgor's plans here at Fort Amol.
I hope you realize what you've gotten yourself into. Once you're in Fahara'jad's inner circle, you'll never get a moment's rest. nnI know this from personal experience.
So, you convinced Lokra to remain. Good. It may not be what she wanted, but it's best for our clan.
Lokra never really had a choice. I'm glad you helped her see that.nnWithout her clan, she is lessened. And without her, so are we.
Did you manage to fill up the supply cache?

Of all the ports in Tamriel, why this one? I sailed all the way across the Iliac Bay and I need a glass of grog!nnI've shared a drink with some unsavory characters, but I draw the line at zombies. I think I'll stay off the docks for now.
We're here. In Daggerfall. Now get off my boat.
The Fangs of Sithis are the property of the Night Mother. We will return them to our enclave and protect them until they are needed.
target: The Fangs of Sithis are the property della Madre Notte. We will return them to our enclave and protect them until they are needed.

source: Thanks for getting those supplies. Quite a few of us have been in need of a good patching up.
I can't believe we survived that! You made the right choice, I think. Anything else would have been disaster.
Rid-Thar will tell you what he can. But know that this choice is yours. You must choose with your heart, and your mind, and your soul.
Look for the truth behind the appearances in her memory. She is a very special young lady.
I trust you, traveler. I know you've made the right decision.
You should find enough uniforms to disguise all of the prisoners in that crate over there.
Tand thought he was going to be sold! This one thanks you for your help!
His life mate <<1>> warned him of the dangers here, but <<2>> did not listen. The son of Muzag is as stubborn as he is naive.
<<1>> attracts trouble like fleas. He'll get his claws clipped one day, I swear.
I almost lost hope! You will always be remembered by this family!
Thunderbug bellies and hive seeds make a fire guardian. Hive seeds and dew bugs make a wooden guardian. Thunderbug bellies and dew bugs, a water guardian.nnIt's up to you.

You released himI think that was the right thing to do. nnI'm glad to know that at least some of the spirits here will be able to rest, though I am sorry for the villagers who remain trapped in the Shadow Wood.
Do not hesitate. This is the only way the Keeper oath is fulfilled and Tamriel remains safe.
Patience, my friend. The race is about to begin!
Please  help me.
Let us not dawdle in this vile place. Find me in the Hollow City and speak to me there.
Rumors say that the people of Zuuk were wiped out by a flu years ago.
All this standing around is bad for my knees.

It seems the Prince of Murder has already disrupted your plan. Where is your army? Surely not even you can hope to take on a Daedric Prince by yourself.nnYou need an army. And you need a safe haven to discuss strategy and gather your forces.
Will the Champion of <<1>> also prove to be the champion of spikeball?
Keep moving. I'm right behind you!
Let's see what he has to say.
Well, don't dally about here, you've got a princess to rescue. It was a princess, wasn't it?
Disaster looms with the Elder Scroll of Altadoon in the hands of our enemies. It must be recovered!

You see? It's clear that Asteril has been dead for some time, so she cannot have been the one you saw in the Imperial tunnels!nnI told yousay what you will about the Thalmorbut we do not have traitors in our midst.

If you haven't seen it yourself, Dominion forces are all over <<A:1>>. They kill anyone who tries to leave.nnThe only good news is they've left the eggs unharmed. We could use your help in learning why.
I guess you aren't an illusion, after all. Skordo also vouched for your existence. He doesn't vouch for anything, so you must have really impressed him.
Ezreba prays for forgiveness.
This mess with our leader needs figuring out, and fast.
My scales itch for a contract.
Damned cultists. Tried to melt our minds and left a giant mess to clean up. Damned inconsiderate.
Was that a vision of Lady Estre? Is there no end to the strange magic of this place?
Do what you must, outsider. Do what you must.
I'm trying to eavesdrop on the conversation, if you don't mind.
The fight is about to begin! May Riddle'Thar bring you luck!
I wish I'd had a chance to talk to that Dunmer before he sped off. What could he know about this?
Finished with your little chat?nnI shall relieve him of his head now and rid us of his insufferable mewling.
You must have mercy! The Dark Elf won't listen, but you will, won't you? nnWe were different! I didn't want this!
Have you solved the puzzle?
<The statue holds the Gem of Preservation.>
Stay alert.
Sadly, they weren't much of a challenge. What's a girl gotta do for a challenge these days?
<The statue holds the Gem of Preservation.>
<The statue holds the Gem of Preservation.>
Your legend grows. Bring this information to our warchief.
Orc! You will pay for this.
So, not overcome by poisonous fumes or fallen into lava yet?
You've done it! Tell Yzzgol what you've learned. Let's end this.
When you're prepared to travel, we leave for Rictus.
I know it will be hard for the community to accept her, but I think this is for the best. She deserves a chance to rejoin the village.
<<1>> pulled me out of the water. Owed him my life.nnNot too late to pay him back.

Thanks to you, my squad has safe passage to <<1>>.nn<<2>> offered to make us part of the Prowler's crew. Don't know if I'll have a choice once the fleet puts itself back to together, but it's better than sitting around and counting sand.
May Y'ffre look after <<1>>. The gods know, nothing will protect his killer once the sergeant learns their names.nnYou go warn that ship. We'll prepare our friend for what awaits us all.
Before the next sun sets, my blade will find a home in the heart of <<1>>'s killer. May the fates guide me to avenge him.
Bright moons, traveler. Merani is grateful she has the chance to improve her aim!
You're the talk of the town. Why don't you come over here and let me thank you?
That foul creature. I expect her to lead the Shadowed Path into Vlastarus any minute now!
Forgive me. You did so much to help a stranger. I won't forget.nnI can open a portal to the temple courtyard, if you wish.
Please don't think me ungracious. Without your aid, I'd still be under <<1>>'s influence. I won't forget.nnI can open a portal to the temple courtyard, if you wish.
If only the bandits would leave us alone, we might have a chance.
Sea Vipers are all over the beach, but the lookout spotted a bunch of them on that island nearby. I don't know what they're up to, but it can't be good.
Stop interrupting, Dark Elf!nnExcuse me, please. What else can Zur assist you with?
The summoner's array still remains. Destroying it should put an end to their assault on Mistral.
I could get used to traveling around with you. It's never dull, I'll give you that.

I will never forgive you for what you did. That relic is going to cause horrible suffering in the world.nnI'm leaving this ship, leaving Kaleen. Perhaps I'll go out on my own. Whatever happens, stay out of my way.

I will be blunt. You were a fool to trust a relic that powerful to these Bretons. If they do not use it for evil, they will harm themselves through their ignorance.nnI believe I am done with both you and Captain Kaleen.

When the elves attack our shores and hundreds of our soldiers die, I want you to remember the choice you made. If you had kept that relic, we could have saved those soldiers.nnYou made the wrong choice.
Your decision at Carzog's Demise will affect this world greatly, for good or for ill. Kasan fears the relic will bring more destruction than good. Even so, it was your decision.nnTravel safely.

Well, after all the years it's taken me to find this place, I certainly did not expect to see someone else down here. nnWere you searching for it as well? Or do you even realize that this is the final resting place of Sabasad the Shield?
Can't you see I'm reading here? Please, leave me in peace.
What is it you want? Wait, what are you holding? Is that  no! He must have sent you. Please, I need more time.
Be cautious! There are some here not friendly to Pact soldiers.
Ears that large and you still don't listen? Perhaps you need a few alterations.nnThere was a time when the sound of <<1>>'s voice commanded the terror of thousands.
Already you waste my time. What do you want?
Welcome back to the Guild Hall! How goes the search?
Watch yourself! This isn't a safe place for soldiers of the Covenant.
Seeing my comrades again gives me hope.  We'll guard the outpost while you finish this.
Choose carefully. I don't want that  thing in our village any more.
I applaud your bravery in coming here, but sharp swords will seek your life if you stay.
The spring in your step! Did you know a sense of accomplishment can alter one's stride? You learn to notice it in others.
You are with the Khajiit, outsider. I know this. Go. Talk to your friend.
The Mane still lives. I trust you have a good reason for this, my friend?
The light of the moon will purge the darkness from the heart of Arenthia.
They think I've no authority here. How wrong they are! nnI am here under the personal authority of <<A:1>>, and when he hears of this debacle, heads will roll. Mark my words!
If the Sea Vipers call up a hurricane, the Prowler won't ever make it out to sea.
I don't know how much the Maormer are willing to listen to reason. But I must try, for the sake of <<1>>.
Please, bring <<1>> to justice.
Happy just for the chance to do something normal. Relaxed. Thank the Green for you.

Ah, the errant deputy.nnI was just informing Headwoman <<1>> of her apothecary's connections to the High Elves of Summerset Isle. Once the torture begins, we'll learn why the Dominion killed their own diplomat.
Get what you need. I'll get what I need in a moment.

Z'en's price! We don't deserve this. We've done nothing wrong. I'm beginning to think our clan's just cursed.nnDriven from our home, then we find a new place to settle, only to have the very earth itself rise up against us ? It's not fair.
Balag hears that you are doing well in the arena. You don't look so tough as you must be.
Congratulations. As insipid as those hopefuls undoubtedly were, you surprised me. I didn't think you stood a chance.
I suppose you're feeling pretty cocky about now. Don't let it go to your head. The qualifying rounds are child's play. nnAre you ready to take on a real challenger?

Welcome back, my lovely! Zara wondered when you would return. She missed you terribly. nnThe other contenders should thank Jone and Jode that championships are not won by physical attraction. Your sleekness would best them all.
Mysterious Stranger, you are truly the Grand Champion! You should consider accepting a position as the trainer here. You could have your choice of divisions!
You're doing the right thing. Go destroy that bastard so my people can live here in peace.

Few have emerged from the forest who were not fleeing in terror. I can only imagine how dark it must be. nnAll the same, this is no safe haven. Driladan Pass is overrun with skeletons led by the undead form of Prince Naemon himself.
The seals  unlock the seals  and I can  break free .
The scribs kept away from that fetching tree trunk. They don't seem to care for it. If you help it do what it needs to do, I have no doubt they'll find their way back to shore.
This isn't a good time for a chat, stranger. Though if you have good news, that would be a welcome change.
Yes?
You got what you wanted. Off with you.
I can feel the spirit's frustration. It wants to help the Great Tree, but something prevents it.
Thank you once again for what you did. Let's not speak of the details. Thorinor has worried enough as it is. You brought us back together, and that's all that matters to us.

You have now witnessed the first sacrifice, and you know that true honor need not be named.n nYou are now one of us. You are Ash'abah.  We will recognize you as our sister and together, we will uphold the sacred duty of our tribe.
Do not be afraid. The Wood Elves have only themselves to blame.nnWe shall never cower in the shadows again.
Oh! You startled me!
The passage to the tower is to the northwest. Go on. And good luck in there!
<<1>> cooks the filthy skooma in his lair. Let's put an end to him.
Who are you?
You'll have to go on alone. Find the Engine. Destroy it.nnSurveying these ruins will have to wait.
I want to heal the Great Tree, but I'm just a farmer. If something is keeping that spirit from mending the roots, there's nothing I could do to help.
You are one of us now. Welcome to the tribe. nnTrue honor need not be named.
Good day to you, and welcome! I hope you didn't have too much trouble with the locals on your way in. Feel free to look over my sundries. Just let me know if you find something you fancy.
Welcome back to the Guildhall. There is much knowledge buried beneath the sands of Alik'r. Have you found any to share?
Please  there is not much time. nnFirst, you must decide  are you willing to join us, to become  an Ash'abah?
What foul magic is this? This  is this the Shadow Wood? nnIt is. This is what the Shade seeksto transform Valenwood into  this. A realm of darkness and evil. It's inconceivable!
Welcome to the Sentinel Fighters Guildhall. You look like the capable sort. Interested in signing up?
Good luck with the spinner.
Today truly is the worst of my life.nnDamned Netches.

Collect the gate key from the coffer to the north and destroy the three crystals to bring down the barrier. There's one crystal in each tower.nnMeet me near the Hall of Judgment's entrance when you're done. I'll continue scouting until then.
Let <<1>> take a look at you. Quite dry for a castaway, and no injuries this one can see.nnDid you hit your head in the shipwreck? Here, stand on one foot. That's a sure way to tell!
If the commander doesn't send someone to help our troops on the shoals, they won't need me. They'll need a gravedigger.
Help me, please! I got caught in this bubble of force, or whatever you call it. Get me out!
I found a note in one of the desks talking about this hatch back here. Guess what's down there?
Sorry, the lodge is off-limits to anyone not part of the Pact delegation. You'll have to move on.
I just need a mug.
Ah, mortal! You are a curious creature.
You've done it. The tomes are gone! I can't hear them anymore.

Who are you? You don't belong in here. Wait, maybe you can help me?nnI ran away from home with one of the bandits, but I've since learned that he was a jerk. He lost my ring in a game of dice and killed my father when he came looking for me.
Quickly. We don't have much time.
We're finally taking control of our own fates again. Long live the Fighters Guild!
Such a pity! The Mourning Stone's secrets would've brought me to the Queen's attention. Once again, <<1>>'s plans stand in my path to glory.
I can't bear to think that we left our people behind in that forsaken plane, but we did what we had to do.
Don't! OhI'm sorry, I wasn't expectingI mean, I am really glad you're not a Daedra.
We need your face to become familiar so your presence won't be questioned. Come, stay by my side.
You do not have horns. This is a bright moon indeed.
This one wishes you hadn't destroyed the books, but the shrine may yet reveal its secrets.nnFirst is first! Determine how to rekindle the flame.
Carry on, soldier.
You no longer wear the husk of the Hollow. Should I bestow it onto you again?
If the inspectors see these rats, we're ruined!
Whoops! I'm sorry. I didn't see you there. I almost ran right into you. I guess I'm a little distracted. Anyhow, I hope you'll forgive me.
Oh, hey, you're the one who's volunteered to drive away the Orcs, right? Chieftess Niriel wanted me to give you these seeds.
Beg your pardon! This is a private residence. Where are my guards?

Z'en's sweet mercy! We did it! The serpent's bound again! nnFirst off, I have to say I'm sorry to the gods for ever doubting them. Second, I promise I will never say that guard duty is beneath my abilities again. Never!
Please return quickly with the tools. If I can't trade them for medicine, this one's father will die.
Want to buy a carpet? How about three? They aren't good for much else.nnYes, <<1>>, even you!
This one hopes the people may be forgiving. Akkhuz-ri can't expect a warm welcome.
Thank you! This one thought we were done for after <<1>> sentenced us to death.nnHow do we get out of the Hall of Judgment? They're not going to let us simply walk out of here.
You've got to let us out!
You've got to help us!
This one will get Kargand the help he needs.
You need to use the book now. Cast the ritual! Don't worry, I turned it to the right page. You won't be annihilating worlds or anything.
Did Marcella send you? Please! Get me out of here.
Please! You've got to help me get out of here! Those crocodiles look hungry.
Peace be upon you, wayfarer. I am relieved to see a survivor from the docks. The news we have received is grave indeed.
I shall return to the council. We have many plans to put in placeboth to assist you in your cause and to prepare for our return to Valenwood.nnGood luck, outsider. And thank you.
If this place remains open, as has yet to be determined, the Clan Mother should hire you in a more legitimate capacity.
You are thrice lucky, but you will never best Ishalga!
What are ye doing here?  I told ye this is sacred ground. How did ye even get past the barrier?
All right, you've had enough time. Where's the skooma?
Thank you. S'rendarr himself would commend your actions.nnGive me the skooma so I can destroy it. I want to finish what I started.
The troops have secured the Chasm. Thanks!
Caretaker Henodras is passing the mantle to Erunor at the Fading Tree now. Hurry!
We will stay here to protect the priestess from the bandits, in case you drive any of them out.
I'm terribly worried about my comrades. Especially my brother Veranus. Mother would never forgive me if I returned to Bravil without him.
Mara bless you, child. Did one of my temple guards send you this way?

Ah, it is my most pleasant and clever friend. Zur is happy to see you again!nnThis Hollow City, it is nice, yes? Gadris would have liked this place. I learned much from our time together. Zur keeps better notes, now. Very neat. Less doodles.
It is nice to see you again, friend. I find the accommodations in this city to be most pleasing.nnI can't help but imagine that Zur would have taken great delight in this place. I think of him often.
We must be ever vigilant. Daedra can be as devious as dark clouds on a sunny day.
You've got to destroy all four of the focus crystals in order for us to open the portal.
Sorry I missed the fight with Molag Grunda. I got distracted by a veritable flood of Dremora. I was up to my ankles in Winged Twilights and was having a grand old time!
Go on in, don't keep the Captain waiting.
Go, walker. Repair and learn.
Bright moons. Jone and Jode shine down on us, even now.
We're almost done. Just destroy those totems.
Thank you, Hallowed. You've filled your role admirably, as hundreds of Moon Hallowed have done before you. You have the thanks of all who praise the Bright Moons.

Only the dead and the desperate end up in this part of the desert. You appear to be neither, so you must be a very brave soul. nnDo you intend to enter the cursed grounds, the Tears of the Dishonored?
So, we meet in person at long last. You looked taller in your projection.
I erect the spine of caution. Adalmor is not the most patient of Nords. Perhaps there are no patient Nords.
Go onrepair one of those siege weapons.
Just stick with the training, soldier.
Go ahead, use that repair kit.
The time has come to perform the ritual and destroy the Harvest Heart. My children yearn to be free!
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
I'm sorry. I don't have you signed up for a fight at the moment.
What  what are you? Are you real?
Hm?
You heard Father, yes? We must pray at the lunar shrines to learn more of his  my past. Let's do it.
Mother said we should pray at the shrines, see more of her past. Come, Hallowed. Let's do it.
We have accomplished great things this day, my faithful friend!
I'm so glad you could come! My parents will be back tonight, and I was afraid I'd have to face them alone again.
This is my test. If I can take the life of this girl, it means that I'm willing to make the necessary sacrifices.
Gifted with a rare and powerful ability, Aranias tried in vain to win her parents' affection.
Peace be upon you, comrade. Good to see you at my little meeting.
By the Divines, it's good to see you here.
You look formidable, comrade. Perhaps one day you'd care to spar with Ra'zaym, yes?
Ahh, so nice to be holding this meeting in Skyrim. Perhaps later we can go for a run out to one of the dragonshrine ruins! Always a good fight, draugr.
You must be the one Merric and Aelif have been talking about. Finally we get some movement around here.
What news do you have?
Our customs and our traditions  these are the things that sustain us in this foul land.
I toil and sweat, but this foul land provides few bounties.
I often deal with the unknown in my role as a go-between and agreement broker.

I am most grateful for your help. Casnar's brother, Enneh, will be at his market stall. The wedding offended him so greatly, he had refused to attend.nnWhether he knows what happened to Casnar or not, let us hope we can soon put the matter to rest.
Congratulations. The path is over. The moons shine their light upon you once again.
None have entered the vault save you and the vicereeve. I have confirmed it.
You again?  You seem to make a habit of showing up just when things are getting properly twisted.
This one will never complain about a job again.
We were lucky to make it back here alive. Those Dawnmead are  they're monsters. Thank you for getting the relics back here.
Somebody here must know why <<1>> has gone bad. Ask around. Discreetly.
Be mindful of your step. This forest has been most unkind to guests.
I really appreciate you helping me out with this wolf situation.
I can't believe they're dead. Glad  glad you could bring the relics back, traveler. Make their sacrifice worth something.
The pillars seal the gateway. Unlock them with the keys.
Use the keys on the pillars and we'll be on our way to Moonhenge. Well, this Moonhenge. Confusing, isn't it?
Those bastards killed Patraud, for little more than stepping into the clearing. I'll be sure to return the favor to these Bosmer savages.
When inspecting all the claws of this plan, this one is not so sure it will work.
We'll find out what we need to know.
I'd be lying if I said I liked Patraud much. The Apprentice never knew when to shut his mouth, but he didn't deserve to die like that.
That Bosmer we  captured mentioned a matriarch named Selene.
By the Egg, those Bosmer were vicious. I won't forget Patraud's sacrifice.nnLet's hope there's research worth doing in this forest.
Told you I'd make it back, didn't I? Not going to let something like a little gutwound stop me. No way.
Honor and praise, my friend. Do you have the Staff of Magnus?
I'm sorry. Only Forebears are allowed in today. We do welcome guests on some occasions, so I hope you will return at another time.
I know you are a guest in our city, wayfarer, so I will forgive your ignorance, but the fellowship hall is open to Crowns only.
Do not worry, I will not get in your way. I like keeping I's head on I's neck.
Accompany Evoker Ahainar-jo. He will attempt to contact the Bosmer again. Perhaps they will tell us how to contact the spirit of this forest.
Greetings, Crown. nnBy Stendarr's grace we have summoned the strength to forgive you for your trespasses.  I hope you will afford us the same courtesy.
Don't you have your own dead to tend to in the Crown quarter? nnLeave us to our grief and we shall do the same for you.
You have our condolences, Forebear. We have asked Tu'whacca to take up your dead. No Redguard should face such defilement.
Thank you. You have no idea what it means for me to see Lorwen alive. And our project fulfilled. You've saved us.
May Ruptga's blessings fall upon the wayfarer who uncovered the truth about our inglorious Magistrate. Crown justice prevails once again.
Greetings, sera. Distrust runs deep here in the Alik'r, but you are most welcome in our Guildhall.
<The imperial is still dead. He will likely continue to be dead for several years.>
We must stop them from destroying my island.
I thank you. If you are braving the cellars further, I would ask again for your help. On behalf of all my people.
What foulness is afoot now? The dead have risen? I thought Alasan was purposefully not raising them!nnWere we too late? Has Alasan made himself into a lich?
I really miss my lute, F'lah.
Hunal has been giving us a running commentary of how it's going in there. Truly, your vision showed me falling to Urcelmo's blade? Raz thinks Jone and Jode do not know him very well.
I can't work under these conditions! I'm not built for war!
Remember, the beacon at the lighthouse will be our signal to move in. Light it once you've completed your task. We will descend upon the Maormer at that moment and crush them.
Leave me alone. Let me die here.
Thanks to you, my soul is back where it belongs.
Freedom is a wonderful thing. And I'm sure that dear Lady Laurent has missed me terribly. She really is lost when I'm not around to help her.
You work quickly and efficiently, young one. I appreciate that. nnDid you recover all the ship designs?
I prayed Tu'whacca would guide you.nnDid you find Zariya? I heard fighting amongst the dead  is she all right?
Don't tell anyone, but I've started sleeping under the desk. The streets are too dangerous at night.
I've a great deal of work to do, so please excuse me. nnI need keep busy. Keeps my mind off things.
Greetings, wayfarer. I'd ask you to report any rumors you might hear concerning disappearances to Justice Istah.
These disappearances have the Justice on blade's edge. Seek him out if you have any information to impart.
Hers is a sad story.

Ruptga's blessings upon you and your house, wayfarer. nnI apologize for the poor state of our streets. The recent unpleasantness in the wastes has brought an influx of Forebears from the westand you know how they are.
Fahara'jad's appointee is useless as a sundial in a sand storm. nnIf this is the best our Forebear king can send, he should abdicate.
You must be the person who rescued all these people. We were part of Vanus Galerion's group before  well, before everything fell apart.nnWe appreciate everything you've done for us.
Got me new bones yet?
My mother banished me to this Crown-infested hamlet with its absurd bumpkin nobility to "cool my blood." nnIt leads me to wonder if she already knew people were being kidnapped here.
I've not seen my son for some time. At first I thought he'd debauched himself into another stupor, but now  now I bear a father's worry.
You missed all the fun.
You have to get out of here before my babies find you. They'll tear you apart! This has never happened to me before. So many people are dead!
This hall is full of secrets. If you will hear advice, then hearkenleave Bergama now before you are caught in the jackal's snare.
If rumor is to be believed, a great many of the disappearances occurred near the gambling hall. I've been giving it a wide berth.
Hmm. You looking for a skull thumping? Keep walking, stranger.
You have returned. Did you ignore the instructions of the Champions as well? Raz hears that is something you do.
Let these petty man-thieves come for me. By Tava's red feathers, we will see this nonsense ended with a flick of my blade.

I knew we could count on you. You have never disappointed me. But there is so much left to do if we are going to win this war.nnStill, with you leading the charge, we have an excellent chance to end the Planemeld and save our world.

My friend! It's good to see you again. I'm thrilled I could persuade Urcelmo to trek out here. We need to support Akkhuz-ri and the Champions. This is a vulnerable moment for our fragile new Dominion.
Hey  hey. You wanna walk me home? I heard there are nasty folk out there, y'know? Dangerous! nnWhy's your face so fuzzy?
Hallowed. I hope you and these Champions won't take long. I worry about Her Majesty's security this far from Auridon.
I know that scent. Green keep you, my friend. The Silvenar and I are well pleased that we could be here to support the Khajiiti people.
My friend! Isn't this amazing? It's my first time on the borderlands of Valenwood. And my first time in a Khajiiti temple! I'm honored to be here today.

It's a shame about all these people going missing, but I tell you, it's great for business. Samhudah's paying me to stand here and make sure no one shady gets in. That's it. nnEasiest money I've ever made.
I've never seen a place like this in all my dreams.Unless we're in my dreams now. That's the only way it would make sense.
I hope to save enough gold to make the journey to Sentinel, but it's hard to come by in this stingy Crown village. They cling to their wealth like a goat kid to its nanny's teat.
I have something for you to do.
Ah, well met! Very well met, indeed! Allow me to welcome you to The Winking Jackal! If you should need anything, feel free to call out. nnOr, you know, throw something. That seems customary here.
The decision is yours alone, though you know what I believe is the best course to take.
Business has slowed to a tortoise's crawl since the disappearances started. nnMany of the missing were patrons of ours  friends, even. If you ask my opinion, this smells like Crown mischief.

Fair winds. Have you come to escape the sour looks as well?nnAs soon as people began to disappear, the guards went looking for the foreigners. I've taken refuge here to avoid harrassment. It's not all bad thoughI'm a fair hand at dice.
Deliver the mixture quickly. If the vampirism progresses too far, curing it becomes a far more difficult endeavor.
We'll both be happier with that altar smashed. You'll see!

All stories go on, even when your part is complete. There was a reckoning for Aranias and for the Wilderking himself, as you well know.nnNow, go where your story takes you. I will try not to interrupt it again.
