Now remove the heart and there may be a chance we can grow a new one.
My friend! They hit me over the head and dragged me in here. Is Alanya safe?

If Andur kills me before I pass the mantle to Aranias, there will be no caretaker of the Valenwood. nnThe forest would become a voracious monster. It would turn against the Bosmer and ultimately bring about its own destruction. You must stop him.
The bundle of roots will pull you into the ground and let you pass under the fire.
Stick close to me, and I'll have that gate open in no time.
If you don't mind, I still have recruits to drill.
Please, go let Pircalmo know what's happened. I'll untie Alanya. We've made such a mistake.
You don't look like one of Gudarz's bruisers. What do you need?
Ranneth untied me? That means Pircalmo is safe, right? He did nothing wrong?
Take out <<1>> and his lackeys will take to the hills. Spineless bastards.
Pardon me, I have to go on sentry duty.nnWhich is a relief, with all these new low-lifes in camp.
A woman named Aranias endangers the whole of the Court of the Wilderking, you must stop her.
I have guarded this square long and long, wayfarer. Even so, I do not know what the Forebears might do about these disappearances. Best that a Crown abide here and keep watch.
Welcome to the Manor of Revelry. Let me know if you see anything you like.
Help me clear a path so we can get <<1>> out of here safely.
Look at you! Nothing but skin and bones! We really need to fatten you up before you wither away to nothing.
The manor is everything you hoped for, isn't it? But look at you! You could really use a bath.
<<1>> is kind of clumsy. He tripped and stumbled six times on the way down here. It's a wonder we weren't spotted.
I don't think I like you. And I don't think my friends will like you, either. nnBetter think about moving on.
I'm a Nordwhich means I'm moody, and prone to violence. Don't provoke me.

You must decide which companion to take on the initial assault. You need to travel light and move quickly, for speed is essential.nnEach of these soldiers has worked with you before. You know what each of them can do and who will serve you best.
Once you select the companion that will aid you in the initial offensive, let me know.nnAs soon as you're ready, we'll begin our assault.
The Fighters Guild came to Coldharbour for this express purposeto stop the Planemeld and save our world. nnNo matter how many of us fall this day, we shall not fail!
Go on, close that portal. The honor's all yours.nnI'll make sure nothing sneaks up on us in the meantime.

Win or lose, it's been an honor to fight alongside you.nnThat said, let's do our best to win this thing, all right? I'm not sincere very often, and I'd hate to have wasted it just before I die in battle.
The Champions are in good hands with you, Hallowed. Good luck on your path.
The expression upon your face tells me that the time has come. The final assault is about to begin, isn't it?
The final adventure begins, yes? May the many Moons bless this foolhardy endeavor!

I enjoy a challenge as well as the next mage, but this might be a little much, even for me.nnStill, I'll do whatever I can to make sure our world isn't completely destroyed. While I grew up on the Shivering Isles, I now call Nirn my home.
Please, you have to hold on. We  we can't lose any more of our companions. There's been too many deaths already.
When I left the forest, I thought I was going to be alone in a new world. But everyone here  it feels like I'm with family again.nnYou're all stuck with me now. I'm not leaving until we finish this.
No longer will we hide in the darkness. No longer will we fear those who would hunt us.nnToday, we become the hunters.

So now we just need to find the other two wards. My apprentice Shiri is traveling with Prince Azah, trying to find answers, but they need my research.nnLet me work. I will ensure you are notified when we know more.
Hurry! If you take too long, these bandits will kill me.
You! There you are! The scholar Zohreh said I might find you here. nnYou must make great haste. Prince Azah is in need of your assistance.
Looking for something? A set of keys, perhaps?
You did it! The portal is ours now!nn<<1>> and <<2>> have already led troops through to the other side.
Here in Willowgrove, we pride ourselves on two thingsour honey-mead and not being stung by bees.
You look like you're at loose ends. Interested in making some money?
I can't believe you beat me. You! A cheat and a swindler, in league with that false matchmaker!
Sorry, I'm a bit busy right now. Have you had a chance to try our honeymead?
If you're not going to deliver those to Zan, I'll give them to someone else.
<action sequence>
We will find Sai Sahan. Your vagabond emperor and I will find a path to the Halls of Torment.
<No text. Indaenir is in an action sequence for this step.>
My men are itching to soak the sand with Imperial blood. We're just waiting on you.
I hear Zara will be picking fighters for the next division round soon. Maybe I should go flirt with her.

My scouts reported sounds of battle along the beaches. This forces my hand. If I can't explain this immediately, my superiors will hear about this and assume the worst.nnI need you to tell me what's going on in <<c:1>>.
Be on your guard wayfarer. There are more dangerous things in Bergama than discontented Redguards.
The Withered Hand rallies more dead to its banner with each passing day, and still these fools feud. Crowns and Forebears taste the same to vultures.

Tava's red feathers! Do I dare to believe my eyes? I have been watching that door for so many days  I had ceased to hope.nnTell medid the king send his army? These Imperials could launch a full invasion if they are not stopped.

Whoever you are, I rejoice that you have come to my rescue. The Imperials have kept me locked in here.nnI deemed it likely that they would seize control of all Alik'r, and there would be nowhere to flee to.
This Khajiit's magic has no equal. Save your dignity and quit now. This one will be Sorcerer Division Champion.
You've seen for yourself. <<1>>'s influence is gone from this tribe.
Welcome. What brings you to <<c:1>>?
I've seen better.nnGo on then, ask what you will.
Do not tell Meridia, but Mezha-dro should have joined Fighters Guild. At least then fighting all these Dremora would pay something.
My axe and pack are outside. Take them with my gratitude. I must do this alone.
The harpies are congregated around this building. Looks like the mercenaries took something every bit as valuable as the harpies' eggs.
By Jone and Jode, I wasn't sure we'd make it out of that one, but you never cease to impress. Things are always exciting when you're around, it seems.
Let's go. My axe won't find a Sea Viper spine on its own.
Lead the way. We'll learn what the Sea Vipers plan soon enough.

We need to search the area for any information we can gather about the maormer's ritual. I'd start by looking in some of those ruined houses and examining a bodies lying around on the broken docks.nnMaybe a few survivors can answer questions, too.
We did it. I can't believe I'm here. My master, Rurelion, would be proud of me, I'm sure of it. nnCome on, it's time to kill Molag Grunda. We can do this!
Tu'whacca has taken the Chief. So passes Marimahwater into sand.  May the Divines bless his passage.

It wasn't easy, but we did it. We stopped the blight from spreading, defeated Naemon's servant, and we still have the heart we can use to grow a replacement for the Eldest.nnAll things considered, this went as well as I could have hoped.
If only I could get to my feet, draw my weapons . nnBy Onsi's bright blade, I would die in combatnot like this.
Tu'whacca, I cannot heed your summonsnot yet. Just a few days more and I will cleave that Withered Hand in two.
This poison strikes like a scorpion  just below the ribs.
Slain by a cup of water  Onsi, forgive me.
Many here are beyond our help. All we can do is ease their passing. Water into sand, wayfarer  water into sand.
Zeht's tears. Our dead, our sacred waterwe've nothing left to revere that hasn't been polluted by these Withered Hand dogs.
Our tribe is beset by sickness. Is this the end of the Ash'abah?
I feel like I can see forever here. Not seeing what I want to though.
I beg your pardon, O wayfarer, but I must hold to my work. Many and many of my tribe-folk require attention.
The Chasm is ours. We'll protect the portal while you push on ahead.
Killing Dremora is thirsty work. I need a mead!
I think  I think I just narrowly missed Tu'whacca's summons, brother. I credit my mother. She had a stomach like an iron kettle.
Tava curse these twisted legs! I almost reached him in time. nnI wasn't fast enough.
If my brother is taken from me, by Onsi's bright blade, I will visit a blood-storm upon the Withered Hand such as the world has never seen.
That's it! Welcome to the Undaunted. Now go make ol' Mordra proud.
And so, the little mortal, once more into the breach!nnI believe the Ayleid King wants you to find a hidden key. Hurry! I think your friends have already made it into the sealed hall.
Well, so far the vampires have remained true to their word. They allowed us to pass through the Orchard without any resistence.nnI wonder how long our good fortune will last?

With your help, we will launch a two-pronged attack into the citadel. It starts with the abandoned Fighters Guild hall within the city.nnWhile the fighters use the secret tunnel to reach the hall, you need to find the key to deactivate the wards.
What are you doing, sneaking up on a woman in my condition?

Hey, I know you. Indaenir mentioned you. You've come along at just the right timeor I guess it's the wrong time. The forest that way is blighted. Indaenir's looking into it. I'm not supposed to let anyone through, but I can make an exception.
Ah, my friend! So good to see you again! Now that my head has cleared, the writing has been going very well. How went the relic hunting?
I'm hoping to compete in the Summoner Division. I finally learned to conjure wolves. Only took me three months of trainingand three lost fingers.
Don't worry about my safety. I'll be perfectly fine.
I would like to speak with you, but I must finish reading this first.

Everything is so  very different. It's like I'm no longer a single physical form, but my being is spread out across the forest.nnAranias is slipping away. You are my friend though, whoever I become. Will you stay for just a moment?
Wonderful! Thought I'd be yapping here for eternity. Blasted Wormies only have eyes for the empty ones.nnVery well, tie me to your belt and we can get started. No time to lose!

You'll find Ugorz in the Orc stronghold to the east, and Zirani in the Khajiit village in the west. Both were once-flourishing townshipsbut no longer. They'll need help to escape.nnI'll meet you all at the Overseer's overlook.
Nice! That'll show 'em!
Please, go away! If the Taskmaster knows we've talked, he'll be furious.

I can't tell if you're crazy or daft, but you have my thanks.nnIf you can stop the Daedra at the other fronts, we should be able to hold here. I won't blame you if you fail or fleewe're prepared to defend our homes either way.
This one knows you mean well even as you keep pestering her. You must, to risk your life to come here.nnBut she has already told you. This one refuses to leave. Taskmaster is watching.
I'll wait right here, and hope no one notices their things are missing. You do this, and you can just take the damned thing.
You-you are here? Thank the gods! We need you!nnThe third Ansei Ward is here. That girl Shirithe scholar's apprenticeshe is a necromancer and she has come to the necropolis. We have to stop her!
Do not linger here.nnThe living who wander in my realm tend to become  lost.
Welcome, stranger. I'm on the hunt, but you're not my quarry.
With Vanus and the Mages Guild to aid you, you've gained a strong advantage in this fight.nnDo not underestimate the power of Vanus Galerion. He's accomplished many great things during his lifetime.
Have you spoken to Malesse?
You didn't hear anything, got it? Certainly not that I'd like to be his night blossom. Or anyone's! Especially not his! You didn't hear that!
My apologies, but I can't chat. Tholbor's given me an arm's length of tasks to do, including his filthy laundry. Horrible man, honestly.
My apologies. I'm all out of sorts. Malarel has a thousand tasks for me, and her idea of motivation is a lightning bolt to the forehead. I understand I'm the third assistant she's had in a month!
I'm the stage manager for the Swordmaster Division. If you hurry, you can make the next round of qualifiers. Credentials, please?
A moment.
Excuse me.
Raz wishes he could help. Naemon would not last long.
A moment. I want to watch this.
Pardon. This seems an important moment.
In a moment. Shazah would like to see this.
In a moment.
Sorry. I'd like to see this.
Not only did I witness the choosing of the Silvenar, I also got to see the Heart of Valenwood. It's really been quite an extraordinary day.
Don't interrupt.
This looks important.
We've been away from the central barrier long enough. Gilraen and the others will need my healing. Let's hope they're not dead.
By the Green Pact those Daedra were powerful! nnI fear what Gilraen and the others are facing at the central barrier. Perhaps we should return to help.
Honor and Faith are due all, but you who have come from afar  your contribution is matched in measure only by the length of your journey.nnThank you.
We have to keep the Sea Vipers out of <<1>>. We must hurry.
If not for your little challenge gambit I'd have killed you by now. Get on with the fight before I change my mind.
My sword-arm hangs loose in the socket like a sagging palm frond. If you have come here to train, I suggest you find a lighter sword.
I thought we were safe here. Hidden from the enemy. The God of Schemes grows more powerful by the day!
I'll just stay here for a while longer. I should whisper a prayer to Y'ffre for my fallen brothers. nnThank you once again.
You're a strong one, aren't you? Khuzi likes the strong ones.
You got Ansei Maja's Ward? Wonderful! Why don't you hold onto it this time ?nnYou need to get the other Ward too, the one Throne Keeper Farvad was carrying. Go on! I'll find you later.
What have I done? What have I done? I have struck down one of our ancestors!nnI have betrayed my vows, my people, my god. Tu'whacca! How could you allow me to do this?
You can talk to them. The fine people inside, where the skies can't be seen. Go on, they're near.nnThey're all near. Above. Below. Who'll protect us from them?
We'll hold them off! Close the rifts! Go!
I've never seen anyone fight like that.nnI mean, you should go.
Anyone could defeat you, with enough training.
Luck is not victory. Watch your back.
Winning one battle doesn't make you a true warrior.
I'm relieved to be out of the Tower of Lies, but I'd be lying if I said I didn't want to be out of this damned place altogether.
We're far from the familiar sights of Stonefalls. But these perils we facethey're epic! They will sing songs of our glory long after we're gone.
You're looking for a High Elf woman? Yes, I saw one pass this way. Right into that strange cave. The one with the village that just appeared out of nowhere!

I stepped out for a moment, dispatched a dozen Dremora, then popped back in. Just wanted to make sure I had the opportunity to see you off.nnWell, off with you, then! So long! Toodle-oo! Don't forget to write! Ta-ta! Cheerio!
Have you found <<1>>? They can't have taken her far from here!
The Ash'abah need your help. Go to the Tears of the Dishonored to the east.nnI pray that my vision did not come too late.
The trail of the Senche begins at the bones of my fellow Hound. I barely escaped with my life, and his life escaped with his bones bared.
Did you find her? Please tell me you did  or at least, that you didn't lose the flute. It's the only memory of her I have.
I've always loved this part of the Chasm. So majestic. Takes your breath away, doesn't it? On occasion, quite permanently.
You really do need to go now. The tribe will return from raiding the Wood Orcs to check on me, and I don't want any bloodshed.
Nielas is back! Thank you! What of the others?
I'm safe. I'm safe. They can't hurt me here.
Go to the circle. I will draw Gorzesh out of his lair and lead him to you.

Good, I can't imagine the source of what's going on over there. Plus Girin went to scout the area. Don't let him flirt with you too much. He's more interested in his own  interests sometimes then the problem at hand.
Thank the gods the ship's stopped moving. I don't know if I can bear going to sea again.
Now that the Fighters Guild and Mages Guild have finally set up shop, maybe this place can return to some semblance of normal.
Fighters and mages can be a little rowdy, but I'd rather have the customers than the quiet any day!
I'm not sure who drinks morethe mages or the fighters!
Where did all these fighters and mages come from? They're eating me out of house and home!
No matter how far from home we might be, the Mages Guild always provides for its members.
I hate this so-called existence.
Welcome back to the Guildhall.nnThe sands of the Alik'r hide all manner of wonders. Have you found any to share with us?
I saw you eyeing my fire. It isn't very warm, but it's all we've got. Go find your own fire, stranger.
I wish we could take longer breaks, but the work never ends.
Escape? That's easy. nnWaiting for the right time to make your move? That's where the difficulty comes in.
Don't run off like that again, Alexis. You know that I worry so!
The Pact may still be active in the area. We will continue our patrol, for we must be ever vigilant.
You return. And with the gold, yes?
Go on then. I have nothing more to say about it. Run back to your kittens!
I can't believe he just blew my cover. Please tell me you have good news?
We'll settle down here in Longhaven until we've fully rested up. Then maybe we'll hit those Argonians back and make them sorry they ever crossed us.
A contest? Grand! Go quickly, before the guards I tipped off arrive. It'd be a shame if they mistake you for the Artisan.
Good luck with that Darius fellow at the Mages Guild. And, of course, let me know if I can get you something.
I'm sorry to bother, but have you seen a mer named Rollin? He was supposed to meet me here. But he's late. Very, very late.
Let's see what Manthir has to say. Oh, I'm so excited!
These should fetch some good coin here in Woodhearth. Thanks again.
Like I said, I'll send troops to the necropolis as soon as I can spare them. nnUntil then, may the gods be with you and Prince Azah both.
A pity you could not do more for us, but I'm sure you have your reasons.
All right, a deal is a deal. You won't see me again.
Welcome to our sleepy little town of Willowgrove, traveler. We make the finest golden honey-meadrare and delicate on the tongue. Well, we do when things aren't all aflutter.
This one is so proud of Yenadar. To give himself so that others might live. Thank you for being honest with me. I know he would have wanted me to know the truth.
Red Mountain Ash, how Thalara longs for it. Seek the tuffs around Lake Rumare. Gather ash for Thalara, and rewards will be yours!nnBeware of other seekers. They will steal what you've gathered.
My guards  all dead .
Curse that Molag Bal!
This is all they send to kill me? Truly?
Get out of my face, milk-drinker.nnI don't need a blood-spitting child like you in my way, I've got winners to bet on.

Greetings, sera. I am a long way from home, but Boethiah has guided my hand to this place. And I knowin timeI will find myself standing atop a pile of the dead, glory backing my hand.nnWhen I win my chance to fight, that is.
Gutter trash. Wait your turn, like the rest of us.nnI haven't put this much thought and sweat into this filthy arena to have a cretin like you butt in front of me.
Ah, another sorcerer, I think.nnWill it be you or I who sees the champion's seat first, I wonder? How could one know of such a thing?
Oh, hello. I'm not entirely sure how I found my way here, but I think I can earn some coin to find my way back to Wayrest.nnIt's been quite a trip, I can tell you that! Good luck, if you're fighting!
Unless you're betting, step aside. This one has no time for peasants and idle thinkers.nnBe ready with your coin if you step in front of this one, yes?
Yes? What's the problem?
Heretry your luck with the lizards.
After a hard day's drinking everyone gets hungry, right? Pass me a few coins, and I'll fill your belly.
I've heard Hadran is dead.nnThugs like him get what they get, I suppose. Makes no difference to me.
You are truly kind to have taken such time to seek me out and return my great-grandmother's recorder.
I take what time I can to study. I never knew warriors had so much to read.
The slime Hadran's been slain, I hear.nnGood thing. Perhaps I'll finally be able to leave this muckhole.
Seems like people are starting to leave. I guess I'd better start packing my casks away, but I'll hold off to whet thirsts until more people have left.nnSpeaking of - want anything?
Come closer, khajiit, and listen well.nnBare your claws to this arena and shed much blood. Come and come to win. Do it for khajiiti. Do it for Jone and Jode.
Have a little chat with your beggar friend, then you and I need to talk.
I see noises  have you seen them? They glow pink and sharpen swords in the moonlight with a caterpillar with fangs.
Are you a pilgrim? The throne is not safe for you today.
You are always welcome here, warrior.
<<1>> knew you would solve Khenarthi's Roost's problems! This one thinks we will see much more of each other in the future. Safe travels, my friend. Say hello to Watch Captain Astanya for me.
Take pity, walker! A coin for pity's sake!

I am glad Pelidil's threat is ended, but the Staff of Magnus is still missing. For now, I have another task for you.nnUndead rise in the north. Bodring and his Vinedusk hold the line. Meet him at Marbruk's north gate and aid him however you can.
I don't know how you found us, but we need your help. The forest has turned against our village, and we've been forced to take refuge in this cave.
You don't understand what you're doing!
It's not surprising that the Khajiit had no respect for our sacred Pact. What else do you expect of an outsider? No offense.

Come to me when you have collected the testimony, physical evidence, and magical omen needed to prove the guilt of the accused. nnWe are eager to put this matter behind us and make peace with the forest.

This is the Thalmor Headquarters, our base for operations in the region.nnThe locals have voiced some issues with our presence, but they recognize the necessity in the face of the Dominion's current troubles. At least, they had best do so.

I take it you ran into Lady Meridia? Lovely woman. Charming. We get on famously! nnWhile you lot were having yourselves an epic row, I gave her a shout. Asked if she'd be willing to help us out if things went badly.
I can't believe Calastil would stoop so low as to steal my heraldic cane just to score a few favors with the queen in my absence!
Can you believe Laurosse stole my husband's dog Pluck? He may have inferior blood, but that's no excuse for such cruelty!
Earrastel's a pretentious oaf, but stealing my wedding gift just to satisfy his vanity? Unforgivable!
The second stage is the most important. What use is magical inquiry if it cannot foster relationships?
I'm  I'm the Mane! Hallowed, we survived!
She's going to love this!

Red Mountain Ash is what I need. And you're just the sort who can bring it to me. Harvest it from the tuff around Lake Rumare.nnIf you see anyone else harvesting ash, steal theirs before they steal yours!

Good journey to you, warrior. I thank the Divines for sending you to me. Hasten to Lake Rumare and gather Red Mountain Ash. Return as soon as you can.nnBeware others who also seek the ash. Slay them to ease your task.
Keep those marauders off my ship!
No passing through <<c:1>>, citizen. If you want to gawk at Argonians, you'll have to do it elsewhere.
Halt, citizen. By order of the Thalmor Inner Council, all contact with the Argonians in <<c:1>> is restricted until further notice.
Was your hunt successful?
Track the troll carefully. The thing is quick and powerful, and it won't hesitate to snap you in two.
Another pilgrim? The Bone Barrow's full of them these days. If I could get anything done, I might be glad for company!
<<1>> wants to thank you for rescuing <<2>> and the rest of the crew. Best go see her before you leave!
Please present your findings to the Treethane, advocate.
Not only did I lose Erinel, my neighbors openly despise me for daring to court a Bosmer. Why, Quertasse paid someone to steal my censer!
Please take whatever you've found to Treethane Rolon, advocate. Everyone wants to be done with this terrible business as soon as possible.
Look for signs of where the wasp landed. A keen sense of observation is the hunter's best weapon.
It's been a few days. The vision alters time. You never really get used to it.
So, you've returned. Tell me, what did you see? Did you speak to Brackenleaf?
There are hundreds of places in Wayrest for a noble to loaf about, but he chooses the sewers.nnI bet all that privilege fosters eccentricity, after a time.
We need to find Master Pellingareno telling what could happen to him down here.nnHe's not the brightest noble.
I can't argue with anything he's said.nnI won't stop him.
Good luck with your trial. I like you. I rather hope you survive.
<A deep rumbling reverberates from within the tree, like the sound of snoring.>
A heated battle. I haven't felt its like in ages. With luck, the invaders will crawl away from this place and leave us to our slumber.
I'd keep moving if I was in your boots. This isn't a friendly place. Not at all.nnYou'll want to follow the bridge. Best of luck and all that. Cheers!

That was  different. After we took down that titan and the Valkynaz, all those Dremora appeared.nnI think your Dremora friend is establishing her dominance. She threw Cadwell and I out, which was kind of rude, but what can you do?
There has to be a bottom. These rocks need to be anchored to something, don't they?nnBest stand back, though. I don't think either of us wants to find out what's down there that badly.
This is incredible! I feel the life of <<A:1>> flow within me! Have you seen my wife? Where's <<2>>? Why hasn't she come to congratulate me?
I'm sorry this puts you in an awkward spot. Truly, Y'ffre and the Wilderking brought you to us in our hour of need.
Quick, close that door! That's a dreadful draft!nnIn the meantime, I'll make sure none of the Dark Lord's minions creeps up on you.
I was afraid something like this was going to happen. Poor Nadafa! She loved to go walking in the dead of night. She said it helped her sleep .
It appears we have come full circle, Vestige.
Lord Varen is waiting for you.
My lord Varen has more to say to you.
You'd better speak to Varen. I think we've given them all something to think about.

I simply cannot believe this is happening. Our father, you . nnPerhaps it is better that you are going. My courage might fail me in the face of such a task. Whatever tradition may say, there is no dishonor in what you are doing, Sameer.

This is too much! Do I look like some kind of powerful sorceress to you? nnNo. I'm just an apprentice. I can't take on an army of Baron Montclair's thugs! I mean, I want to advance within the Mages Guild, but they ask the impossible!

Honor to you, Sera. Welcome to the Guildhall. I realize that our presence here in the temple is unconventional, but I'm afraid that our former hall was razed just recently. One does what one must, yes?nnWhat can I do for you?
Watch the little adepts play at sorcery. This one thinks they will make good members of the Mages Guild one day.
There is no time to waste. The Elder Scroll of Ghartok must be returned to us!
You are too late, Sameer. Your father is dead  even worse. Some Elven necromancer  he turned your father into an abomination!
My father's blade. It's strange to see it again after so many years. I will use it to strike down our enemies, in his name.
It's not as it seems! I love Almur with all of my being. Why would I do anything to hurt the ones he loves?
I don't know who you are, but if you seek the one responsible for the johads, you do so backwards.nnCome. Jahi should hear this as well. I'm tired of secrets.
Welcome to the hall! What can I do for you?
Just when I think I've read all the books we have here, someone brings in another ancient tome.nnIt seems I'll be reading and categorizing for the rest of my days.
I felt every blow as if you were hitting me, but the creature's death has put an end to the pain. Praise the Eight that our tormented flesh has been put to rest!
This one heard your words with Nabira. She spoke the truth. Zaddo can tell you where next you should go. Where the paths of moonlight lead you.
Ahh, yes. The Bright Moons spoke of you to Saifa last night. She sees their light in your eyes, even now.
Get yourself gone. The situation in Arenthia can only get worse.
Good day to be alive, isn't it? Everything's just as I remember it! Always gratifying, that is.
You've been gone awhile.
You've been gone awhile.
You've been gone awhile.
All honor and glory to the brave Covenant warriors who returned the Elder Scroll of Ni-Mohk to us!
If <<Az:1>> can control <<Ac:2>>, perhaps the shades will settle down. Then we can get back to excavating <<Ac:3>>.
Keep an eye on Tharn. Remember, he's a politician. That means he knows nothing, but thinks he knows everything. nnJust bring Sai back in one piece, all right?
The Mages Guild has no record of shades haunting this location. Where did they come from, and what do they want?
You're going to take the she-troll? She has all the subtlety of a stampeding mammoth in a pottery shop! Good luck. You're certainly going to need it.
Time has not mended their mistrust. No good can come from taking both Abnur and Lyris with you. You must choose one, and only one.
You did it. You did it! I'm free, I'm finally free!nnThank you, thank you!
It's truly terrible what has come upon the village, but I promise I'm not the one responsible. It's my duty as Spinner to teach the children about the Green Pact. I would never violate it.
I wasn't sure if an outsider would be found guilty of violating the Green Pact, but I guess it was Aranak who cut the flower.

My friend, I am sorry you had to be the one to end Lleraya's troubled existence. It was unfortunate, but necessary.nnAnd now if we are to save Rivenspire, we must engage in another unfortunate act. The time to deal with Baron Montclair is upon us.
Despite my myriad talents, I must maintain a supply train in this backwoods marsh.nnWe have excess stores. Feel free to peruse them, if you like.
Sorry, not doing any business today.
Tell the vampire that he has our support.nnFor now.
I won't beg, but I implore you to restore my son. I have waited so long for this moment.
The Khajiit are a marvelous people. I am blessed by this opportunity to enjoy their company.

Do you think Molag Bal actually reads this stuff? Er, sorry. Trying to help my brother find something useful here. But look at all these books!nnI always wondered what a Daedric Prince read at bedtime. Some of this stuff is pretty disturbing!
How could a spinner violate the Green Pact? Madness.nnOh. If you're hungry, the meat was untouched. So we can trade, if you want.

Things will be strange until we have a new spinner. I don't like how that feels, especially after such a potent violation of the Pact.nnBut it's good to be able to go back to business. If you want to trade, ask.
And so it ends. I pray that it has, at any rate.
You're not going to get all weepy with me, are you? I mean, I've got that stoic reputation to maintain .
Honor and faith to you always, my friend. My part in this is over.
Yes, this will be close enough, I think. Are you prepared?
Eranas, really? I can hardly believe it. He was a good man. Well, he had his reasons, I guess. We all have our reasons.
You will not be sorry, my friend. I assure you that my days of aiding man-eating serpents are over!

Eranas was just a scapegoat, to distract us from their real intentions. Did you see what pattern his sigil made when it was destroyed? Ancient Ayleidoon for "thorn," which is what the spinner was. A thorn in their side, so they plucked him out.
Amazing. The person in the village most in tune with the Green Pact somehow violated it.nnLike that never happens.
My priestess, returned to me at last. Long did she suffer in the clutches of Molag Bal, yet you have brought her to me.
A pretty stone, yes? But it will remain dull as an old torture puppet until you've filled it with Daedric souls.
Less talking now. More killing.
What are you waiting on? Find me another tear now so we can move on.
While you were gone, we had a few visitors. Nothing Adusa couldn't handle, of course. But we shouldn't linger in this place much longer.
Even with Shaman Bogham curing me, I feel like goat dung.
Thank again, friend. Some may forget the Wilderking. Many more will never know he existed.nnNot me. I will remember.
I should not have had all that garbage dung water  I should have listened to Gluth.
Malacath's teat, my guts are still on fire. This was spider venom? Was it as big as a house?
That was even worse than the time I ate rotten kagouti stomach.nnWhich was as bad as it sounds.
moving around easier
moving around easier
moving around easier
moving around easier
moving around easier
Razum-dar sent me here to await your arrival. He wants you to join him as quickly as possible.nnIt seems Vicereeve Pelidil came this way after stealing the Staff of Magnus.
I owe you my life. My Lord calls you Vestige? A strange name. Is it true your soul was taken from you?
I don't know how long the blood you gathered will slake Marcel's thirst.nnI hope it's long enough for us to make our way to <<1>>.
Now where did that greedy little captain run off to? I'm ready to hit the waves!
You actually found other townsfolk? And you brought them back here? Remarkable!
Not a bad location to make a stand, it's far from perfect though.
You've done well, my friend. The Mortuum Vivicus is destroyed.
This is no place for idle travelers. Turn back.
My head  make the pain stop! Please, do whatever you must to make it stop!
I knew I should have done a few more deep knee bends before we rushed into battle.nnGo on, go on. Don't let me slow you down. You still have a world to save, you know.
Great gifts often appear as a surprise, but sometimes, the surprise should be spoiled.
Stars above, it's good to see you again.
Who are you? Can't you see I'm having a drink with my friend here ? nnMight as well embrace the crows; they're here to stay. If anyone goes, it'll be us, not them.
Divines be praised, you came back. Can we get going, please?
I didn't think anything short of my death would sate Gargak's bloodlust. We may still end up at each other's throats one day, but for the time being we can enjoy a little peace. We owe you much.
You obviously aren't a frightened refugee. Welcome to Camp Tamrith, a little slice of home in a hostile wilderness. It isn't much, but it's better than nothing.
I hate this, but there's no other way. By the Light, my sister must die with honor before the evil completely overwhelms her.nnOh, Arkay, grant me the strength to do what must be done.
<<1>> is currently off-limits. You'll need to keep back, for your own safety.
Last I saw <<1>>, she was taking shelter in one of the tents.nnI could do without this damnable rain. It's been storming since we arrived, and it shows no sign of letting up.
I can't bear the sight of him.
Wait. Did you hear that? It's the sound of you not killing each other! It is the most boring of sounds. Beyond mudcrabs mating underwater. More of a "clump  clack  clump  clump."
What a terrible shame, losing <<1>>. Even if she was kind of mean to me. At least Reezal-Jul won't be stirring up any more trouble.nnNow all we have to do is take care of Lleraya and Montclair.
It is done. The Amulet of Kings is ours once again.

The time has come for us to enter the catacombs of Sancre Tor. Do not underestimate the dangers that await us. nnIn ages past, Sancre Tor was a place of light, but I fear that is no longer the case. We must be prepared for anything.
I know we don't stand a chance against Molag Bal unless we recover the Amulet of Kings, but I'm still uneasy about this. That damned thing has been nothing but trouble from the beginning.
I'm not one to hope any creature suffers, but with <<1>> I'll make an exception. She can spend eternity in <<Az:2>>, for all I care.
Sebazi hopes to hear you've killed your quota of Gray Vipers.
Rumors swirl that the Gray Vipers have suffered losses of late. May we thank you for this?
Back again, eh? Now, which contract did I give you?
We must find Sai Sahan. Everything depends on that.
My estates, my titles, my own lifeit's all forfeit now. All in the name of preserving the Empire.nnI swear by all the gods, Mannimarco will pay dearly for this.
I thought you had left me! Please don't do that again!
Lyris is safe, and whole once more. You have done well, but there is still much to do.
My brother's wife can't take much more of this. And truth be told, neither can I.
This place stinks of dust and death. Let's finish this and get out of here.
Do you really think this is a good time to stop and chat? The Redguard needs your help.
Sorion is very much aware of the depths of his talent. That can rub some people the wrong way. I do hope he hasn't landed in trouble he can neither sing nor play his way out of.
Beware, these roads aren't safe.
Careful there, traveler! These roads aren't safe. Bandits about.
What's wrong? You look like you've seen a wraith. nnTharn's been gone for hours. I think he's up to something.
An unexpected visit! What brings you back, Vestige?
Welcome to the chasm my friend. We're nearly there.
I hear you helped rid us of that bastard, <<1>>. You have my gratitude, friend.
So, <<1>> is dead, eh? Well, that's a bit of good news, I suppose.

Hmmph! I can't believe the king's being so over-cautious. I asked to borrow one of the Ansei Wards for a few days to study it, and he flatly refused! nnI'm still glad you got them back, of course  we make a pretty good team, I think.
Please excuse me. The stablemaster already rebuked me for negecting my duties once. I would not wish him to do so again.
Etienne  I'm sorry I failed you.
Where is Etienne? He should be back by now. Where could he be?
I'm nearly out of supplies, treating all these wounded guards. nnIf you have something to ask, be quick about it.
Stay back - I don't want to be coughing blood on you.nnThis whole mess  It could've been avoided, somehow. We weren't ready. We couldn't have been.
Let me know if you see movement, friend. I've gathered the other archers' arrows  it's just a matter of putting them in the witchmen.
Let them come! We're as ready for them now as we ever will be.nnI have all of Malacath's strength behind my axes - none of these toothless savages will topple me, now or ever!
I've killed a fair few of them today, but they just keep coming.nnFine by me. My arms aren't tired yet.
That's my home. Over there, the one on fire.
How could this have happened? This is our home! Evermore is just across the lake, and this is all we get?
Imagine, all these crates lying around and no guards in site. It's a real shame.
Don't worry. I'll make sure no dead men make off with this unattended cargo.
Shoo! Away with you! Stay out of my garden!
I hope you've not come looking for the queen. She's left all matters of state to Duke Renchant. I heard Her Majesty's tending to the indigent masses at the chapel.

She brought the book here. I followed, but it's a witches' covendozens of themtrying to use the book for some evil ritual. nnI'm just a novice. I should return to the guildhall in Hallin's Stand. If I'm not here when you return, meet me there.
Brave meeting. Mind your tongue in this place. Too many ears and not enough brains.
Forgive me for stating the obvious, but you're alive!nnWe heard some terrible noises in the caves below. What happened?
Amazing powers, you say? Well, I can't wait to test your theory and see what happens!

The ritual is prepared. Wyress Rashan assured me that you'd have the heart.nnAssuming you do, tell Rashan, and we can get on with it. We don't want the forest to suffer a moment longer than it has to.
Well  I expect you won't be returning any time soon to enjoy my sisters' hospitality, and I can guarantee we won't run into each other on some city street .nnSo I guess this is goodbye then.
Good luck in locating <<1>>. I'm sorry I couldn't be of more help.
Such a shame about King Eamond and his son. Both of them were so dashing. Renchant is a very poor substitute.

I tell you, things grow darker here by the damn hour! nnReachmen are right down there! Came in by boat, took the lighthouse, and now they're crawling up in the woods to assess our defenses. And our orders are to just sit here and watch!
Must be nice to be able to travel between this realm and the physical realm. I'm stuck here. Yes. I'm stuck here.
Welcome back to the guildhall, my friend. nnThe history of Bangkorai is rich in lurid and bloody events. Have you brought us any regional books or journals?

Aha! I thought we were in for a bit of easy coin with this job until the queen said you were coming along. Now I know to expect danger.nnBring it on though. If the plan goes awry, that just means we get extra hazard pay.

Surprised to see me? Sounds like I already missed some interesting experiences. A Hagraven controlling crows? I want to see that!nnThis business has potential too. Of course, our part only comes into play if there's trouble. Let's hope there isn't.
The sky is beautiful! A little different to what I remember.nnBut the Walking City. I must find it, so I may finally return home.
We don't take kindly to strangers.
I would rather not speak to someone I don't know.
Glad to see new faces in the village. It gets lonesome seeing the same people, day in and day out.nnIf Kerbol doesn't mind, maybe you can stay a bit longer.
Head right up those steps to leave the village.
Well fought! Sai Sahan travels with worthy companions.
Go now, before the Goblins find you.
Do you mind? I'm trying to have a quiet moment to myself here.
Reynelle was a kindly oneshe entered these Vaults with us, and I'd like her to leave with us, if the Mad Architect hasn't scattered her soul across Oblivion.
We long for freedom.
Now! The heart!
So, we're to stumble blindly into the catacombs beneath a crumbling ruin abandoned for an age? Lovely. That bearded idiot swordmaster will lead us straight into a trap, no doubt.
The Wyrd expect an alliance now after they murder my daughter in cold blood? They're lucky I don't have them all killed here and now!
I can't wait until this war is over. After this, I'm due for a vacation.
I'm in your debt for finding me. Elgenie says I'm going to be fine. I think Abir was more relieved than I was.
I'm not sure what you're hoping for with the girl, but I can tell you, she won't leave this ruin.
The captain will soon realize the right decision was made.
So those abominations the Dark Witnesses are herding about were once people like you and me. You should speak to Delphique. She may have something to say on this.
Perfect! One of Elgenie's I bet. This will do nicely.nnOnce you've destroyed the stores, use what's left of the poultice. It'll let you return to camp safely and quickly.
Happy to hear that <<1>> has been destroyed, but it's a terrible sad thing, what happened to Crestshade and Camp Tamrith.
Already the woods are defiled by habitation such as this. We can never recover.

Think of the glory! It'll be just like Ranser's War! We'll rescue Rivenspire and the women will swoon. It'll be great! You'll see. nnGo on to Shornhelm's chapel and tell Countess Tamrith I recruited you to the cause. I'll be along as soon as I can.

Well, that went better than expected! Not one breach of our perimeter! Guess those Baandari are good at something more than just swindling  ah, I shouldn't have said that. nnThe Knights of Saint Pelin are indebted to those cats. To you, too.
You have shown me more kindess than I deserve. I shall spend my remaining days attempting to atone and truly honor my son's memory.

Hmm. Well, there is a thing about the poultices. We do not have them just yet. nnThe good news is that I had foreseen the need for them, so I sent our herbalists out to gather what they needed. But  they haven't returned yet.
This is all the fault of the Bretons! We've been perfect neighbors, and this is the way they treat us? It's deplorable!
They took my brother. It was the Bretons. I'm sure it was.
I'm not sure what everyone is complaining about. I feel much safer now that the Fell's Brigade is here.
These Bretons are always so quick to blame others. It's a wonder they even get along with themselves.
Tell the most honorable guard how you heroically drew your weapon before chasing after that mangy cur!
Ah, you must be <<1>>'s agent.
We dislodged House Montclair from its nest. The upper city is ours and Shornhelm is free.

I can't believe that Baron Montclair would order the brazen kidnapping of Shornhelm nobles. Even if it was his general, this Reezal-Jul, who carried it out, Montclair is at the root of it. I am shocked.
<<1>> has accepted you, then? Good. We need all the help we can muster.
If they don't stop yelling at each other, I may just have to grab a switch and tan some hides. That'll give them something to cry about!
Deepswimmer doesn't fear alligators, but he fears trolls!nnThanks for saving this one's hide!
<<1>> sent you? She thinks, perhaps, you can do work for us? Who are you to know so little, yet offer so much?

Remarkable! What a strange sensation of new recollections and old. I believe that Reezal-Jul somehow removed those moments from my memory. But you were able to restore them.nnAnd now you understand what we are facing.

I know we're having problems, but I'm certain that Constable Agazu can handle it. Why the mayor allowed the militia to mobilize is beyond me.nnIt's like we're under martial law. And they closed the inn! What happens when I want a drink? What?

Are you as hungry as I am? I'm completely famished. The thrill of battle does that, you know. And flirting with death makes food taste so much better too.nnWe'll have to have a feast later. Yes, when the garrison's cleaned up.
Ah, sweet-bringer! Thank you for your kindness! You have saved me from many sleepless nights!
You look like someone who appreciates the finer things in life. I'm afraid that's in short supply right now.
Friend, you. Grateful.
Hey thanks again for all that stuff! It'll really help, you know?
Won't forget your service. Means a lot.
So much pain, it's  it's too much.
If only we had the full force of the Mages Guild behind us. These Reachmen wouldn't last long.
Walker  we may never be able to repay you for what you have done, but thank you.nnMay you dance with Jone and Jode until the end of days!

Have you heard the story of the shipwrecked Argonian? He swam from Summerset to Bal Foyen in under an hour. When the messenger arrived with word of the shipwreck, he was warm in bed with a flagon of mead.
Thank you again for finding my lost Puddles. I'd be so lonely without her.
Can't believe it's come to this. I should be leading my clan out of the Strid right now.

These animated boneswhy do they seek to keep us from the relic? Are they the lingering remains of the Ayleids who once dwelled here, do you think?nnWell, they won't stop me. No matter what their reasons are, my cause is greater.
My dear friend, Verandis. I'm glad you're here. You've always been so good to our family.nnI  I never really thanked you for that.
Who invited you into our camp?
I'm going to do one last perimeter sweep and hold the north gate. Don't worry, if anything gets past us, I'll be there to help you.
What brings you into our midst?

Needless to say, this behavior is more than a little disquieting. Short temper is not one of Arkay's blessings.nnI will reserve judgment for the time being, but if he is corrupted  well, let's see what unfolds.
These fools tricked you into doing their bidding. So be it, this isn't the end of me.
Oh, hello again. I'm still waiting on a few more signatures before I can head back to Valenwood. But maybe they'd take some books instead. What've you got?
Are you a member of the Daggerfall Covenant? We need your help!
My fool of a husband can sell apples. I see an opportunity that'll make me rich!
Are you all right? Crazy Eye saw you fall! She was worried you might not get back up!
Be careful. We've been raided by Imperials for days now. Are you here to help us rebuild the camp?
<<1>> said you're headed off to kill more bandits. Keep good count, all right? I bet him it would be less than a dozen.
Dark anchors here, now? The Daedric Prince Molag Bal is surely making his presence known in Bangkorai.
I'll always treasure Dame Marcelle's sword. Perhaps it will encourage me to take up a life of honor and adventure.

Of course, the Fangs! It all makes sense now. Blessed Almalexia had a vision that the Prince of Schemes had sunk his teeth into the ground at Gil-Var-Delle.nnThe fangs she saw in her vision must be the devices Meva described.
Greetings, guild-brother. How may I help you?
Fight now, talk later.
<This bottle seems out of place, balanced on a dagger. Something seems to be inside.>
I've had it right about up to here with the Bitterhands! This has to end.nnAdusa has put much thought into this.
Good luck out there. The Blacksap are a violent bunch.
You did well, my friend. Adusa would fight at your side any time.
You should get back to <<1>> as soon as possible. He'll want to hear what we found.
Nice work. We'll get this information to the rest of the Ravenwatch as soon as I meet my contact.
Nice work. We'll get this information to the rest of the Ravenwatch as soon as I meet my contact.
Nice work. We'll get this information to the rest of the Ravenwatch as soon as I meet my contact.
I do not seek to offend you, but  you look like troublethe kind of trouble we do not need in Fell's Run right now.nnI would suggest you simply leave town. There is nothing for you here.
Leave me alone. I'm only here for the wine.
You can always look, dearie, but don't touch. I'm a barmaid, not a trollop.
What do you say? You interested in having a bit of a laugh?
I suppose a public trial is for the best. If anyone learns we're holding <<1>> and his sons, it might rally support for another rebellion.nnAt least with a trial, there's an end to this conflict.
Can I ask your help? My husband and our dog are missing. I can see the red eyes of the undead from here. I'm worried  we're both capable with a blade, but he's no match for the undead.
<<<1>> makes a sad sound as he looks to the north.>
What a dreadful place you've discovered. When you want to return to Northpoint, just let me know.
Find my knights and bring back Arkay's relics. They are our only hope now against the dead tide.

That's the first time I've seen Queen Arzhela in the castle in days! nnThe people love her so much. I hope she returns to the throneit would be so good for the economy  assuming we don't get slaughtered by the Reachmen, of course.
Take as much time as you like, my friend. nnIt's only the High King and the entire kingdom of Rivenspire waiting.
Burying corpses once they begin to stink is one thing, but when they've been in a damp cave for days? It's like eating hot stew on a summer day. No one likes that.
Take care of that crown, it means a lot to the people of Rivenspire
I'm glad my sons are alive and safe. I just wish they would stop bickering.
I respect the High King's decision, but I can't hold my tongueI have serious doubts about Queen Eselde's ability to rule.nnI hope she proves me wrong, or all of Rivenspire will pay the price.
I respect your decision, and that of the High King, of course. I will do all I can to support King Alard.nnI do worry about his militaristic tendencies, though.
You draw ever closer. Graccus holds my book, the Oghma Infinium, in the ruins below.
I almost feel sorry for young Dorell. Almost. But I learned long ago, if you're going to drink to excess, you have to face the consequences.
You've returned. What have you found?
I heard you and the Prophet talking about Abnur Tharn.
Nice work, "Hallowed." I hope your visions weren't too frightening.
Balance will be restored before too long, I think! With laurels, wine, and crushed velvet lining, yes?
Have you secured a meeting with <<1>>?
I'm not selling anything, friend. You'll have to go inside and talk to Sabir.nnMy part in this business is in acquiring the items we sell and managing relations with our partners.
<<<1>> makes a sad sound each time he looks toward the north.>
I'm just here for when the fight breaks out.

My husband, <<1>>, went for a walk yesterday morning. Said he wanted to get away from the squabbling at Elden Root. He hasn't come back!nnI went looking for him this morning with our dog, and now my dog has wandered off!
What a pleasant surprise, to see an acquaintance from Glenumbra. Good to see you still have your health.nnIt's such a shame, isn't it, that our looks are always the first to go.
You have shown me more kindess than I deserve. I will spend my remaining days atoning for the wrongs I have done.
You have shown me more kindess than I deserve. I shall spend my remaining days attempting to atone and truly honor my son's memory.
Hallowed. Strange to refer to you by that title after everything else you've done for the Dominion. But then, I suppose this was ordained in the moonlight, yes?
This one is humbled to stand before the Moon Hallowed. You have done so much for Akkhuz-ri's people  more than he has done in some time, he thinks.
Who are you? You don't look like a skeever.
I signed on with the Shornhelm Guard because Baron Dorell is a man of action. He's someone who gets things done.
Well, now that we're a big happy family, you should have <<1>> go over the plan so you know what to expect. It's going to be brutal. I can't wait.
I'll do my part, just get into position and do yours.
If it wasn't for you, <<1>> would have been a meal for a spider.

I take <<1>> at her word, and I'm sure there's a good reason for the delay. But it looks bad when she can't construct a simple building for the people she's sworn to lead.nnI do hope <<2>> can clear things up.

<<1>>'s betrayal could not have been more absolute. She knew the details of the ratification ceremony, which puts <<2>> at risk.nnIt's my sister's own fault. She thought to appease <<c:3>> and the Mane by agreeing to this foolish process.
Don't think to start any trouble. None of us are in a forgiving mood.
Firaelion's a little shaken, but he'll be okay. I won't let him out of my sight again for a long time, you can be sure of that.
Your victory will be remembered. We could feel the death of Brinarch through the earth beneath our feet. Even the insects will not mourn him.
You did it. And Wyress Nyronie's sacrifice pays off. Now we only need to contact our other sisters and drive out the remaining Reachmen.
I'll do what needs to be done.
I look forward to your final show of prowess.
Did you use all of them? I do hope you paid close attention to their effects.
I've let the High King know how much of a help you've been. Killing Maugruhl, by the way. That was especially impressive.
I brought <<1>> into custody. Of course, we can't question her without special permission from the Thalmor Inner Council.nnPolitics.
Apologies, I'm a little overtaxed in here. Not much time to talk, I'm sure you understand.
The Prowler is ready to sail when you are.

I should warn you. Ravenwatch Castle is as strange as the man who owns it. His family is very old, and they have  strange traditions.nnDon't worry, though. I have no doubt about the fact that he is on our side. You may rely on anything he says.
There's no use for anger. I can't say I'm happy to be here, but at least we're alive.nnAt least I know my father is still alive.
As soon as Marien is rested, we're going to head for Shornhelm. Try to put this all behind us.
I heard you talking to Lothson. Don't worry, I'll be fine. The big galoot has it in his head I'm some fragile thing. But  it would be nice to have the necklace back.
This one will need some time to consider what Verandis told you.nnVerandis is gone  I still can't believe it.

How many times must you tell a fool not to stick her hand in fire?nnOnce, and she burns herself and realizes it hurts. Twice, because she remembers it wasn't so bad and tries again. Three times? She burns to a crisp and doesn't live to try again.
I don't know you, and I don't care to know you.
You actually got the bow? Incredible. Did <<1>> give you much trouble?
This is it. The monster's lair. But no sign of Zungarg. This is  discomfiting. Keep your guard up.
Mayla and I are going to stay here a little longer. You don't have to worry about us. We'll be all right.
None of this feels real, but your help has made it easier for my brother and I. Jowan's trying so hard to be strong for me. I guess I need to do the same for him.

Today is a fortuitous day indeed for Rivenspire, though I fear other kingdoms within the Covenant may not be so lucky.nnI know that my husband considers you to be his champion, but I wonder if you might be willing to assist his queen as well.
Tread carefully, Vestige. Mannimarco's agents are everywhere. The King of Worms will not be pleased that you stole his prize captive from the Halls of Torment.
Get away from me. You're lower than the Vinedusk.

You've already done the Dominion a great service, but I need you to do a little bit more. It is finally time for the unification ritual, where an ancient ritual will prove I am fit to lead our people against our enemies.
I have a bad feeling this isn't going to turn out wellfor me.
I've half a mind to go after Nedras. What in Tamriel possessed him to leave me like this?
Once I publish my research, you will be able to read all about my findings. I'll be sure to acknowledge your contribution!
Damn him. Damn that stupid old mule. To think I'll never see him again, to give him a swift kick in the rear.
This one is so proud of Yenadar. To give himself so that others might live. Thank you for being honest with me, traveler. I know he would have wanted me to know the truth.

Ah, it is good to see you, my generous friend. I came here to pray to Mara for forgiveness for my past, and it was like the clouds parted and the sun shined on my soul.nnI have decided to stay and devote my life to Mara. It is a better life.

We'll finish patching up these farmers and then send them south, toward Fell's Run, at the first opportunity.nnMeanwhile, go find Darien. And if he's lollygagging with some lonely farm girl instead of working, punch him in the head for me.
I think I heard a troll up near the <<1>>, so I picked up my gear and returned to the city. I don't know about you, but I wasn't eager to tangle with a troll!
During their raid the Imperial Legionaries left our pavilion alone. I guess they're not all idiots.
This region has an incredibly rich history. I'm sure there are vast repositories of lore hidden in these hills and valleys  if you know where to look, of course.
Cursed Imperials. Shooting arrows at us from behind rocks and trees cowards all, I say.
Take the taciturn <<1>> with you, will you? I don't want to feel her slicing me to ribbons with anything but her eyes. Not until everyone's free.
Thank you for retrieving our goods, friend. At least the wounded won't go hungry now.
Do you feel the power? Can you taste it?
Thanks for your assistance with the Imperials. Now we have to deal with bandits of a different kind. These Baandari plan to gouge us, I have no doubt.
Bested by twig-boned Imperials on our own ground . nnShameful.
Well, that was demoralizing, wasn't it? nn"Your death matters little, Emeric." I can't believe she said that! I don't know though. Is it true?

We'll remain here to secure the area. Once Dominion reinforcements arrive, we'll figure out how the Covenant was able to conjure that portal to begin with. nnAnd if they try again, we'll have a host of armored soldiers waiting on the other side.
I hope <<1>> is ready for <<c:2>>  assuming it's ready for her, of course!
She's a braver woman than I!
The mine may be lost, but with these notes I can at least continue my research. Thank you.
Face the consequences. The rest of Adeena's family is in Sentinel.
Do you feel that? It feels like another presence just entered the ruins.
It's strange to think that Najan and I will never speak again, but he deserves it. He deserves worse.
Participating in this ceremony means you accept the blessing of Mother Lamae. Will you proceed?
We lie about like whipped dogs. Ufa drags his feet, waiting for aid. Can he not see that none comes?
Hallin's Stand is a fine city. Lots of good stone work and deep bones. It should always be free.

The real mystery is what's a woman like that wanting to do in a place like this? nnShe has a prisoner, but the Chamber of Passage is not a place for holding someone, it's a place for sending someone on!

I would take back what I did if I could. I just  I didn't know things would turn out this way.nnI thought that, for Dutheil, it would simply be a matter of finding new work. I didn't intend to destroy his life. His mind.
Stop interrupting, Dark Elf!nnExcuse, please. What else can Zur assist you with?
You have all the tools you need to save <<1>> with you. That greedy and cowardly man has few defenses.
I just want to see my mother and father again!
We slipped the farmers out and sent them south with a few soldiers. Now I'm ready to break a few Montclair heads!
Mind the furs. It takes hours to comb out the snarls.
Lovely day for a drink, wouldn't you say?
We follow the Green Pact in this home. Respect this, and we'll do the same for you.
My father thinks he's the alchemist in the family, but mother always said I'd surpass his skills.
The new treethane is a joke!
You should go. I'm not playing this lute for you.
I know you, brother. You're one of us, even if you don't know it yet. Hircine calls you. His song is in your blood.
What happened to you? It looked like you were in a daze for a few moments.
Leave me. There's nothing you can do.
I may have little time left before the Imperials find me. Let me pray in peace.
Your kin live among the mortals. They may be wearing rags or crowns. They may hide within or rise above the masses.nnFind them. They await.
The Baron was just filling us in on what was written in his son's journal. Spell or no, Ellic has a lot to answer for.nnIf he's even still alive.

Thank you. Take this vial and fill it with the waters from this basin. The water must be taken by the one who carries it. With that done, make for the falls that feed into Gil-Var-Delle and pour the water at each crest. Nature will do the rest.
Oh, I know you! You must be the one her beautiful ladyship has been expecting!
Would you look at that line? We're drawing more people than in <<1>>!
You look pale, my child.
I was wondering when you were going to show up.nnWant a bite?
Did you pick up the crate? I'm certain that <<1>> in <<2>> will assist you if you ask nicely. nnWell, I'm not certain of it  but it's worth a try.
Welcome to <<1>>. I'm rather busy today, but I'm sure another merchant can assist you.
Do you have them? You have them, don't you?nnOh, I shouldn't get my hopes up. They fell in the sea, didn't they? I knew it, I have the worst luck.
Look at them, limbs so sluggish and carapaces dreadfully dull. When you've raised the shalks since they were pupae, it gnaws at your heart to see them so listless.
You didn't drop a single one, I'm impressed! Come to think of it, I have been needing an apprentice .
Oh, Edouard, you foolish man. Now look what you've done.
Have you found anything I could use? I've told our guests I'm still preparing, but they're eager to hear my stories.
This High Elf thinks that his people rule over me. The Wood Elves follow King Camoran, not some High Elf Queen! Am I right?
This Wood Elf doesn't realize he would be dead without Queen Ayrenn and the Altmer.nnSuch disrespect. We risk life and limb to save them and they thank us with  accusations and insults!
Now, where did I leave that scroll?nnYou'll have to excuse me. Just doing a bit of housekeeping.
I overheard what <<1>> intends to do in order to pad out his research journal, and if I wasn't still sickened from this poisonous spider bite I surely would be now.
The wine's just over there, in the alcove.
All the Children of Yokuda are dead or gone. We did it!
I'm glad that you've learned to come to me when you are seeking knowledge!nnIn this case however, you will have to look elsewhere first. Say  away from me.
They're so cute together.

Oha visitor. Greetings. We don't get many walk-ins these days. "Curfew and regulations" from what I hear. nnCouldn't have been easy getting past all those Imperials. Maybe you should think about membership in the Fighters Guild.
Wouldn't trust Ludippe with my coin purse, but his eyes are good enough. Let's have a look inside, shall we?

Is that? Yes! I can tell by the runes. The slight alterations in the design and structure is unique to the Valenwood Ayleids. I would be greatly interested in reassembling and studying this tablet if you are willing to part with it.
If that gold is getting too heavy, I'd be happy to carry some of it for you.
Is he breathing? Tell me he lives.
Dammit! That's Kaleen. See to her. I'll keep watch.
Welcome to the guildhall, friend. Found any interesting books or scrolls? Please just place them on the desk. nnWe had a grimoire come in yesterday with troll fat all over it  so safety first.
Ah, that's better!

Tell this High Elf she's being ridiculous. Yes, moon sugar is used to make skooma, but Khajiit use it as a spice! It's a facet of Khajiiti cultural cuisine!nnMoon-sugar shouldn't be regulated because some people use it for the wrong reasons!

Set this Khajiit straight! Moon sugar has important cultural significance to the Khajiiti, but some peopleespecially the Khajiituse moon sugar to make the drug skooma.nnMaking moon sugar illegal hinders skooma vendorsand that's a good thing.
Thank you. Take this ice rune. Captain Gemelle gave it to me to freeze the webs trapping the others. It should make them brittle enough for our soldiers to break free.
<Scouting mission notices and reports are posted to this board.>
I thought for a minute he would start making sense now  but I was wrong.
This one can't believe we have to go all the way back to <<1>>. The last time we were in Arenthia, <<2>> hitched a ride on a cargo ship and ended up in Senchal!
This one must escape!nnYou have seen them, yes? The vampire skeevers?
Why?
No, I'm all right.nnYou saved <<1>>'s life by killing her brother. You should probably speak with her on the matter.
<A notice for a Warfront mission has been posted to the board.>
<No new bounty missions are available.>
<A notice for a battle mission has been posted to the board.>
<Scouting mission notices and reports are posted to this board.>
<A notice for a warfront mission has been posted to the board.>
<No new bounty missions are available.>
<A notice for a battle mission has been posted to the board.>
<Scouting mission notices and reports are posted to this board.>
<A notice for a warfront mission has been posted to the board.>
<No new bounty missions are available.>
<A notice for a battle mission has been posted to the board.>
Pardon me, walker, do you have a moment to help out my lunatic boss?

This Khajiit thinks he can walk into this forest and kill and maim at his leisure.nnHe may not follow the Green Pact, but I do, and I'll have him learn respect for the flowers and the trees before this day is done!
You, there! Do you scout for the Imperial invaders? Is that why you pass this way?
Take this ice rune. It should make the webs brittle enough for my soldiers to break free. Good luck.
Hm. For some reason, looking at you makes me want to vomit. My emotions just feel like they're going to burst out and run away again.nnOverall though, I am feeling a little lighter on my feet.
Really, I hate constant interruptions. If it weren't for my friend <<1>>, I'd never have come to visit.
These people will never forget what you've done for them. And neither will I.
Speak with <<1>> here, or move along. I have no time for you.
What a damn joke. I knew I shouldn't have moved away from the sea.
I used to find comfort in the desert winds, but now I only hear voices.
Nothing left but the clothes on our backs. I'll never forgive the Imperials for what they've done to us.
This is terrible! I've lost everything and that smuggler doesn't even care!
<<1>>'s wounds are too great  he cannot dry up like a puddle on the desert sands. nnHe deserves to meet death like the mighty warrior he is.
Hello there! I'm so glad you came by!nnI think I'm about to make a new friend, and you know what that means?

Do you see how grey it is here? Everything is grey. Just like my life. nnOne long chain of miserable, lonely days  each one worse than the day before it. Do you know why it is that I even bother to get out of bed?
If you find Sir Dubroc, tell him that unless he's making progress against the Reachmen, he needs to get his buttocks back down here.

I hope you're getting more insight into this than me. Every time I think I have it all sorted out, I realize something doesn't make sense.nnDo you think you know what each of the Raiders' names and professions were?
Never thought I'd see the day. And here Tholor and I were thinking of taking on apprentices of our own! Haha! Could you imagine?nnThanks, wayfarer. You're certainly a force to be reckoned with.
I don't like your face.
I don't care who you are, if you can't carry my luggage you're useless to me!

May the Hand of Auri-El guide us to greater peace than exists in this moment.nnNo house or kinship should suffer undue strife from within, and that is exactly what the Dominion is encountering now. Troubling.
Getting the leaders to cooperate will be no small task. I hope you're up for it.
Isn't it exciting? The Mage Guild actually asked us to come with them on this mission! It seems our hard work is finally paying off.
We shouldn't speak, I could get in trouble. <<1>> can explain, I'm certain of it.
The soldiers don't want us speaking with outsiders. <<1>> can explain. She's by the northern barricade around <<Ac:2>>.
According to my calculations, the chances that the leaders of the three alliances can reach any kind of agreement is seven-hundred-and-fifty-six-thousand to one.
Guard duty on a tropical island? Sure, why not?
I hope this invasion goes smoothly. I've got more than enough scars for one lifetime!
Use the repair kit first, then go talk to Aurorelle.
I remember you! You're the reason my master back in Stonefalls almost ate me for dinner! Thank the Divines I was able to hide in that chicken coop.
I pray these talks go smoothly. We need to learn to work together.
Be respectful in the Queen's presence. I'll be keeping an eye on you.
Keep your steel sheathed in the presence of the High King, or you'll answer to me.
Ever get that feeling you've walked into a place you don't belong? No? Think about it .nnI'm saying you don't belong here.

Fascinating, isn't it? To think that such a tiny rock could hold so much power. Can you feel it? It's like it's calling to me. Like the moons call to the tides.nnImagine what the relic it came from could do!
What're you looking at? The song's over.
Do I come and bother you while you're eating? No? Think about that while you turn around and walk away.
I brought enough food for an army but without the performers bringing in the crowds I'm worried it's all going to spoil.
Hey there, milksop. You stared an ancient, unfathomable evil in the eye, causing you to question your sanity, mortality, and very concept of the self yet?
I love every one of the stories Noryon tells, but I hear the Magic Act is beyond belief, so I'm going to keep checking back until they start.
My friend, this table is for the worthy, the bold.nnAnd this one thinks you don't look like either.
Pray pardon me, I wish to keep company with my friends here. Perhaps we could speak another time.
You must be .nnYou must be  you must be  incredibly stupid to come talk to me.
Huh?
Move along. It's been a while since I stabbed anything, and I'm getting itchy.
Step away  step away, you  fool!nnOr I'll make sure no one will ever remember your name! Because all they'll see is a fool who's been  beaten into the ground.
Do you hear it? Sithis calls for you. Tempt me and I'll take you to him.
Go away. I've got nothing for you. This table's for the Undaunted. What counts as Undaunted in these parts, anyway.
Are you Undaunted? No. Get out of here  uh  daunted.
I don't care to converse with strangers.
I don't speak with outsiders.
The Empress of Bone does not wish to speak with you.
Scamper along now little one. Felvyn's a fool, but he's an Undaunted. Good for a story, at least.
I only need one good eye to send you to your grave mongrel. Best you be off. This table's for Undaunted only.
Looking for any work not related to carnivals. Let me know if you have any leads.
Would you look at that line? We're drawing more people than in <<1>>!
What sort of mischief have you been up to now? No, don't tell me. I'm keen to guess! nnUm  is it larger than a breadbasket?

I sell adventuring supplies, kit, and the like.nnI'm open for business, but I'm warning youtry to steal from me and I'll knock your teeth out. I've got a necklace I'm working on, and I can always use more teeth.

I, Boeuf Sterone, have no fear of thieves. For first and foremost, thieves do not steal food if it's poisoned!nnMy food is not poisoned, trust me. It's a trick to ward off the thieves, yes? Anything you buy from Boeuf Sterone is safe to eat.
Well, that's something, at least. Now we can get this ceremony business out of the way. This rabble will learn what a true ruler looks like.
Huh, who are you?
You should speak with Glaras if you wish to join the Briars. Otherwise, I have nothing to say to you.
I understand you attacked Fort Greenwall? Word travels fast in Riften, and I am eager to hear of your exploits.
Thank you once again for seeing my brother safely back to the village. He may cause my hair to fall out before I've seen a thirtieth winter, but I don't know what I'd do without him.
You've made Ivarstead safer for all, and for that you'll always find welcome here.
You're back. What happened? Did you stick something long and sharp through that crazy lizard's blackened heart?

How long does it take to count our pay? Go talk to their elder. We deserve some compen  compla  gold for all the trouble we've caused.nnBeen through! All the trouble we've been through! None of it in the contract, either.
It feels damn good to get out and swing my weapon. As my father used to say: "Idle minds are Oblivion's playground, idle bodies get fat."
I believe you and I have nothing more to discuss. Know that were it not for your deeds, I would personally avenge Lyris' death here and now.nnThe thought tempts more with every passing moment.
It has been a while since we've spoken, Vest friend. You look well.
Never much time to chat, it seems. <<1>> wants to know how well we've fulfilled our contract, and you're the only neutral person around.nnI hope you can give a good report of our work.
They speak in circles, like city-people do. What do they mean? And why do they smell so much like the harpies?
You can't leave us out to dry. We're good, mostly honest fellows. Trying to make a living. You're not so different than us when it comes down to it.
You know how hard we worked for them, right? Toughest job we've ever had.
I don't see Althen. If you have questions, that's fine, but at this point, I'm counting on you.nnYou don't want to disappoint the Ring of Daggers, do you?

Damn bastard Gavendien! Did it all for the jewels, and got away with it, too!nnHe got me good. I'll survive, but he cut Lauravieve's throat. He didn't have to! He just did it to prove a point. I thought I could be cruel, but he is a monster!
We did everything they told us to, but somehow we still failed. How will I ever make this right?
They were using my mill, the bastards! And look what they did to the poor jeweler!
I'm sorry, but the jewelry shop is closed for today.
No, no. I'm not going anywhere. I'm going to stay right here. Yes. Right here.

Praise the Eight! Did you kick that stupid thug's teeth in? I don't know what was worsebeing held hostage or smelling that ruffian's breath!nnWhat about the robbery, though? Did you stop them or did they get away with the jewels?
I can't wait to see my father again. I hope he's all right.
Why? Why would they kill her? She was cooperating! She gave them the jewels!
I'm yours to do with as you will. Whatever you decide, I will go along. My fate is in your hands.
Don't feel bad. I knew Julien was a hopeless case. A man who's sick in love is a sad man indeed. nnI feel sorry for him, really. Enlisting would have probably helped set him straight.
Remarkable. It appears to be an intact volume of Ayleid lore. If it's real, then this is what we came here to .nnNo. This can't be correct.
Nice of you to finally join us. Those damn Montclairs have locked me out of my own city!nnIf any of my people have been hurt, I'll kill Montclair and his daughter with my bare hands.
Qariar is the Blademaster of House Dorell. He's a good man. See what he has to say about all this.
You can reach the Pass by traveling west along the northern coast. And when we get there, I intend to make Montclair pay for the damage and sorrow he has brought to Rivenspire.

It seems that some of my loyal subjects have become dissatisfied with my leadership. Think that I have been blinded by the Light that shines so brightly around me.nnWell, to Oblivion with them! To Oblivion with him! I don't have time for this now.
If we don't get Gwendis out of there soon, those restraints will break and she'll feed on the nobles.
Without <<1>>, we will be hard pressed for help, but we'll get on, somehow.nnThank you again, my friend. For everything.
How wonderful it is, to have everyone safe at home! We owe you everything, my friend. I do hope you'll visit. We could go to the windmill and you can tell me all your stories!
Thanks again, friend. We never would have made it out of there without you.
Destroy the <<1>>. It's  it's the only way to make sure this never happens again.
I'll be more understanding with <<1>>. I promise. With Federic leaving  mind you, I still don't approve. But she is a good lass. She doesn't deserve what I did to her.
I knew it! You lost your spine, didn't you?nnThat's fine. I'll be here a bit longer if you get it back. Otherwise, goodbye to you and your stupid Shornhelm Guard.
You're right, again. They do.
I must tell you the rules before you ready yourself for the race.
There is no way I'm sticking around here to shovel horse dung for the rest of my life.nnI got big dreams, and I got the skills to make them happen.
I'm glad that my daughter's happy, but I'm not sure I can ever trust Dulkhi. Not after what happened.
Hmm. You know, that's the first time I've seen Countess Tamrith in her full armor. She looks so very  yummy.nnI mean regal! That's what I meant!
He's really gone, isn't he? The mighty Verandis.nnI hate this! I really hate it!
