Well done! I'll follow in a moment. I find this room strangely calming and I want to look around.
What is your decision? We need your help.
Did I see the flutter of butterfly wings? It must have been a trick of the light.

Oh look. You're that nosy, fobbing arse who talked me into joining the Shornhelm Guard, aren't you?nnTalk about a nightmare. All that marching  I actually prefer to be here in the stocks, and it's clearly where I belong.

Hey there. You the one Queen Maraya bought passage for to Sentinel? All right.nnI'm just glad you didn't bring along a chest full of luggage. We got to row out to the Posset in this little dinghy here. Real glamorous, eh?

My friend from Hoarfrost! These two wouldn't be here if not for you. You should be proud.nJulien and Shuga have turned out to be great soldiers.nnMartin couldn't cut it, though. Abandoned his post one night. I hear he's back in the stocks again.

I'm really enjoying the soldier's life. The thrill of battle, the rush of victorythese are real feelings.nnI'm thinking about staying in the Guard. Mad as it may be, now that I know Guendeline's waiting for me, I don't really like her any more.
Strange times, my friend, strange times indeed. And you know what strange times call for? A drink!

I'm not the seer my grandmother was. She didn't need to hear any gossip. Oh, no! She knew long before anyone else what trouble I'd be in. How I miss her!nnTell me what happened; the bones are unclear.
Doom has come to Craglorn! The stars have vanished from the sky! nnWill no one listen? Will no one help?
Stay safe out there. Lots of things that want to kill you.

Thanks again for everything you've done. I'll take some time with the amulet to see if it could be of further use to us.nnIf you're looking for other ways to aid us, Hara might have some suggestions on where to go.
Glory has no patience for the idle. Go prove your worth against the Reachmen in Shor's Stone.
I'm just going to sit right here until all this nonsense between the nobles blows over.
Montclair is responsible for all this madness? Hard to believe. He was always kind to me.
The city is safe now, and do you know why? Because Baron Dorell took charge and showed Montclair's lackeys the business side of his boot!
The Light shines on Shornhelm and the Countess! Thanks to them, the city is safe again and Montclair is on the run.
They say the city is safe now, but how can they be sure? Baron Montclair's followers could be all around us, waiting for another opportunity to rise up and strike!
They say it wasn't really the Baron who attacked us. It was some kind of mad Argonian. I never did trust those overgrown lizards!
Welcome back to the Hall! How goes the search?
I suppose I'm lucky I made it out alive, but by the Three I'm glad you came along.nnIf I'd failed here, I think my captain would've had my head.
Good, good. I think I'll have a sit down out here. The wind seems very gooey, doesn't it? Very squishy. Ugh.
Don't worry about me. I'll be waiting here with these rented guar, my carts, and the stench of decomposing guards. No rush.
Soldier, report. What brings you to Ash Mountain? Did Holgunn send you?
Damn those Covenant bastards! It seems like they're fighting us at every turn.

When I was a kid back home in Riften, we'd kill any mudcrab we saw. Ensured they didn't get out of control.nnThat's how I feel about these Covenant soldiers. If we don't kill them all, they'll just keep coming.
I left the mines to breathe fresh air and swing my blade for the Pact. Then I get posted to this place. I think I'd rather go back to the mines. Hah!
Three guide your blade, soldier. Get out there and make us proud!

Thanks. Not many willing to help these days, especially a dusty Ashlander like me.nnWe'd planned to rest up at the Davenas' farm near Kragenmoor before passing through the Deshaan gate. He should know it.
I am so doomed.nnAnd it feels like there are a dozen horses dancing the Wood Elf frolic directly behind my left eye.
Is there something I can do for you? I really am rather busy at the moment.
Thank you for your help, I feel better knowing you're out there helping look for my Puddles.
That was considerably faster than I expected, thanks to your assistance.
Thank you for helping Priest Marnest. I feel better with you accompanying him. You never know if there are any more of those damn vampires hiding nearby.
Don't ask me why we're here. I have no idea. Someone seemed to think we needed to be here to keep Stormhaven safe.nnI haven't seen the rest of the kingdom, but this part's as dull as dirt.
Get out there and find the last of them. Northpoint won't rest easy as long as a single one of Lleraya's vampires remains within its walls.
I don't know how much more of this I can bear. nnWaiting for the general to call us back to the fight against the Ironhand Ogresit's gnawing right through my nerves.
Bad time to visit the city, traveler. Might want to move along.
Hurry, hurry! I'll meet you outside!

Well, hello there! I certainly hope you've found something worthwhile to read in your travels. The selection here has been rather slim. I've resorted to reading cook books! nnOn the plus side, the dinners I've made taste much better.

My Lord Vivec, I bear the most grievous news. Belronen Telvanni challenged me to a duel of blood. I regret to say I won.nnIt was a small cut upon the arm, enough to settle the matter. But he fell dead!
You must go to Bramblebreach. There is nothing more to say.
You have my thanks, traveler. And the thanks of every guard in Skywatch.
Hey there. Saw the carts, eh? Sorry, nobody out here but the help. The Queen herself is still in Vulkhel Guard.
My brotherthe plague boils his blood and ravages his body. I fear he doesn't have much time, but he wants to talk to you.
It's terrible. My book's gone. Years of my life wasted!

Oh, look at me! I'm a terrible mess! You really must excuse my dreadful appearance. I haven't been feeling very well lately.nnBy the way, you haven't seen Nostrum Breva, have you? She promised to bring me more of the Maulborn curative.
Do you hear that? It tastes like yellow .
We're a family again thanks to you!

It is good to see a friendly face. Greenshade is a far more exciting place than Raz expected.nnHe hears now that the Staff of Magnus has been stolen? As if these rebellious Bosmer rebels weren't trouble enough!
Don't come near me! Are you real?
You're not a daedra. What's going on?
You are a miracle worker. Without your help many people would still be in the clutches of the daedra.
You've done the fallen warriors proud. We completed our mission. That's got to stand for something.
Please. Stop the Maulborn and destroy their ability to make more of this damn plague.nnJust be careful. The chamber ahead is crawling with an army of plague husks.
You are a miracle worker. Without your help many people would be dead or dying.
How very strange? What in the name of Oblivion were the Maulborn thinking when they mixed these toxic ingredients together?nnOh, are you back again?
The Eight guide your hand, traveler. You may be the only one who can restore this holy site.
Though I have no sense of sentiment, I am able to understand that her intentions are natural and even have merit.nnNonetheless, there are larger matters at stake here. This is the way it must be.
Stendarr guide your hand. You may be the only one who can restore this holy site.
Welcome to the Guildhall, knowledge-seeker. What brings you here today?
Please, hurry! I know you can do this. I have faith in you!
I can't leave the tree! Erunor and I must stay here as its last defense! Go, help the villagers below!
You did it? Well done! I never doubted you for an instant.nnNow, let me have the mixture, if you please.
If I were a few years younger and my hands were still steady, I'd do this for you. But I'm not and they aren't, so you're just going to have to go over to the alchemy table and get this done.
I hope Nilyne can put those healing herbs to good use.
I love listening to the sounds out here. It's rather peaceful, don't you think?
Three keep you, traveler. Welcome to the Davon's Watch Guildhall. What brings you to our doorstep?
Hello. I understand you've been helping Hara study the Celestials. We're truly grateful for your aid.

Do you know how much gold I've spent to get my wife here? And now the Maulborn have stopped providing their curative?nnI'd trade my entire estate if it meant the plague would release its hold on my wife.
Hello again, my slick-scaled friend. Have you been to the Armature yet? And did I ever tell you about Emberflint?
Mimic the water and flow and we will have no cause to inflict angry pain upon each other.nnThe Maulborn discarded these crates, so now they belong to us.
Those damn Maulborn stink flies! They refuse to give us the curative, just because they call us lizards and look down upon us.nnSo we'll take the curative. As soon as we can find any.
We were hoping to find something good in these crates, but the Maulborn don't seem to throw away anything valuable.nnTake whatever you want. Especially cheese. I hate cheese.
You're so lucky! Verandis never let's me go on dream-walks with him.
Traveler. How goes your survey of Zabamat? Have you found Hightide Hollow, as yet?
Don't mind my good-for-nothing egg-siblings. They're young, bored, and stupid.nnRest assured, I shall continue to remain open throughout this time of crisis.
Why'd we ever come to this island? It's so out of the way. At least <<1>> promised us extra pay for this.

Life is so precious, and so fleeting. Don't let it pass you by. Take time to feel the caress of the wind and listen to the way it carries the sound of your true love's name.nnMirilir  I never did hear anything so sweet and so dear.
I'm rather fond of Estre. High Kinlady Estre, that is. So noble, just, and Altmer through and through. She'll keep us strong.
Who knew that so many afflicted would flock to the Serk! All these people. They're so  sick.
Welcome to Shrouded Hollow! Will you be sojourning with us? Or are you simply a visitor?
These are dark times, and the Star-Gazers are a shadow of who we once were. But our role remains more important than ever.
Always work to do! Keeps one very busy, yes?
The Sword-Disciples are still in thrall to the Serpent. Anything you can do to put them to rest would ease my mind.
I've heard there are atronachs tearing the land apart to the east. Rare ones, even. Unseen for centuries. I wish I could see for myself!
If you would receive knowledge, you must give knowledge in return. nnWhat have you brought me, Seeker?
I will seek out these monks once I make sure everything here is all right.nnI will see you soon.

What happened to you out there? You look horrible. Think of the legendary scars you'll get from those wounds!nnYou'd better head back out, or I'll beat you to the center of that Citadel. Soon as Roaring Ramavel and the others get here.
Hermaeus Mora's shrine is in the deepest part of the archive. I have an unusual relic from the Dragontail mountains to trade for the knowledge of the Celestials. I hope it's enough.
Greetings! I am Vanus Galerion, head of the Mages Guild. I have need of your assistance.
Good luck with that Darius fellow at the Mages Guild. And, of course, let me know if I can get you something.
In time, the body you and Valaste have formed for me will fade. But with this charm, you'll never forget our trials together. The decision you made. I take comfort in that.nnAre you ready?
The court has heard tale of your deeds at the Sentinel Docks, Wayfarer. Perhaps you have some advice to offer our great king in this time of need.

Here is a person who looks noble and respectable. Yes. Razum-dar thinks you would be perfect to act as Queen Ayrenn's envoy.nnIt is a very dignified task. You should be honored that this one even asks.

Get down and be quiet. We don't want to give our position away.nnWe're keeping an eye on these Red Rook bastards. They're not the simple bandits they pretend to be, that's for sure. If you want to help, go talk to <<1>>.

When I was young, I studied all the tumultuous times and the heroic deeds from the first era and I always wished I had lived back then instead.nnRecent events have made this era more interesting though. I realize nowthese times are good too.
I wish you the best in there. If one Nereid caused all of this, the power she wields will be frightening.
I can't believe it. So many dead. Our whole city in ruins. All because of those damned mages.nnPlease, you have to help us.

Arch-Mage Yamanu-ko is in this tower. We call it the Apex Tower. The arch-mages of Elinhir have occupied it for centuries.nnIt was our duty to protect the city. Instead, we leave a legacy of destruction.
Thanks for all of your help!
Hurry. We need to channel the elemental infusions so that we can force an opening into the staff.
That was sickening. I had to get rid of it. He just left  the body here. By the Light of Aetheriuswhat was he doing with it?nnLet's get out of here. We have a ritual site to find.
Go on! Hara waits upstairs.

It was this being all along guiding the lizards this Hist. An exile. Shunned by others of its kind, forced to live here. I cannot blame them.nnYou bested the rest of her minions. Slay the one she calls Treeminder, and her fate is ours to decide.
I thank you, my friend. From the bottom of my soul, I thank you. I don't care where we go, or what we do. What you've given back to me is priceless.

Many believe the Nedes were barely more than barbarians, but ruins like this prove otherwise. Don't underestimate their cleverness. Look for a pattern if you can, and consider the possibility that the lock was designed to be impossible to open alone.
See you there.
Strike the Lost One down. It is the only way to end this.
The Lost One waits below. Do not delay.
That invitation is around here somewhere. Keep looking for it.
Go on. Search through Danni's things. Invade her privacy. I hope you have fun doing it, too.
I hope Danni doesn't find out about any of this.
What did you find in that trunk?
Enjoy your stay on Abah's.
They're out there! Those creatures in the water! I was at the water's edge and I saw them, looking up at me from beneath the surface. Hollow, pale eyes. nnWe have to get out of here!
Keep an eye on those tentacle worshippers by the staircase. This one would have gutted them already had Sali'ma not intervened.
We're going to take the Gray Barrows and use it for the new hideout for the Thieves Guild. I'll need your help.
The owner will be pleased you came to the Lass! I'll be sure to tell her! What can I get you?
There you are. Great! I've just gotten the boat ready.nnWe can get started whenever you're ready.
Hello there!
A bit of generosity for an unlucky soul?
Once the Lost One falls, we will become the Mage once more. Do not delay.
There is no more time for us. You must not delay.
You have my thanks friend.

You're so desperate to live on, short as your lifespan is. I'd be impressed if it weren't so futile.nnOnly the Warden remains. You could turn and run now, if you'd like. After all you've seen. But I think you'll push on. Go! Slay him! Or die trying.
You have my thanks friend. I should have no difficulty replenishing my stock now.
You got the 10 pieces but you lost them?
And who might you be? I suppose you're wanting to go into the Archive? Great. Another raiding party.nnWhere in Oblivion did Brulo get to?
What'd they say?
"Step 2: Extract Ingotsnn"Bring your iron ore to a Blacksmithing Station. Make iron ingots from your ten chunks of iron ore. This is called 'extraction.' If you want to know why, ask a forge-wife."
Tell me the good news, fish.
Speak with Vexa. She'll have more information for you.
Don't break that device. I don't want to make another one.
Get Nick to quit his crying. I'll meet you at Abah's Landing.
So it was true, then. Those crazy High Elves really were the Celestial Mage? Unbelievable!
Another visitor?nnAt least you seem less offensive than that Orc over there. Slightly. Avoid the upper floors. That's where the Learned One dwells.
Again you accomplish the unfeasible. Even in our mortal forms, we each could challenge armies. Mortal potential is staggering.
I have no time for idle chatter. It is most unfortunate the Learned One broke the seal.nnDistractions from rabble like you are precisely why we locked ourselves away in the first place.
Good work, rook. Gwen and I are going to catch our breath real quick. We'll meet you at the Gray Barrows.
Go! Hurry! I'll follow, and meet you back at the Gray Barrows!
So many distractions of late. The Learned One does not wish to be disturbed. You would do well to stay away from the upper floors.
I may not have fully processed that ale, but don't worry. I'm sober enough to steal a ship from a dangerous pirate group.
It's bad enough that the Celestial Warrior and Mage have been turned against us. nnBut what of the Thief? The legend is of the Guardians three. I wonder what happened to her?
You're making a name for yourself around here already! Good, good. Frail, old scholars like myself must rely on people of action, especially in such difficult times.
This one said going by an ancient, cursed Yokudan fortress in arid mountains was a bad idea.nnBut nobody listens to Khajiitbecause all they do is sit around eating Moon Sugar all day, yes?

Don't mind me, just fixing our wagon. It's not built for this sort of terrain, but it's not as bad as Sallunas makes it sound.nnWe came out here to be the first merchants on the scene, but the disappearances have been bad for business.
I've always wanted to study the Citadel of Hel Ra up close. None have been inside since the First Era.nnBut many of my fellow Redguard who entered have not been seen again.
Good work, rook. Gwen and I are going to catch our breath real quick. We'll meet you at the Gray Barrows.
Good work, rook. Gwen and I are going to catch our breath real quick. We'll meet you at the Gray Barrows.
Ah, our first test. The gatekeeper blocks our way. Let's see how well you do in getting past her, Rook.I'll keep my mouth shut on this one.
I'll let you talk to the gatekeeper. I don't want to blow our cover.
The gatekeeper's blocking our entrance. I'll let you speak with her. But I'll be watching how she acts. I don't trust these guards.
Ssh! Stay down! We've been followed.
Move on, then. Nothing to see here, is there?
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course fast enough. Would you like to try again?
Talk to Ahmat. This one just creates the challenges. Ahmat does all the jabbering.
I tried to join the Black Horse Couriers, but they sent me to do these races. It's not that I'm not a good horseman. It's the pressure of the course that gets to me.
One good turn deserves another. What do you need?
I owe you much, my friend. One day, your kindness shall be repaid.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
The sun here is too hot. And the sand burns this one's paws.
If you plan to run Ahmat's course, I wish you better luck than me.nnMy horse succumbed to a terrible thirst and bolted for the nearest oasis. Nothing I did would urge it back to the course.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
To devise a course worthy of a queen is no small thing, yes? This one hopes it is a good challenge for her Majesty but that she remains safe from harm  this one hopes, at least.
What are you talking to me for? You have a course to run. Follow the markers until you reach the end! Talaya will record your time when you're done.
Is this is to be Talaya's final course, then it will be her greatest. nnIf this one must face the prospect of spending all eternity here, then she will spend it refining this course to perfection.
Of all the tortures I can imagine, nothing could be worse than this. nnTo be stuck here for all eternity without a horse? No! This cannot be!
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
There. If this Rigurd the Brash character does not adopt this course as part of the Konunleikar then he simply does not like horse races. nnTalaya has given him the best course this land can offer.
I told Ahmatthis is my homeland. I know this place like the back of my sword-hand. I will make short work of this course. Now I just have to find my horse .
Where is that little milk-drinker? Did you see a little Bosmer running around with a horse?nnThat horse is mine! He stole it!
Designing a horse-racing course in this forest is like trying to weave a new shirt using sticks and stones. The raw materials Talaya needs are simply not here.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
My skin prickles with the heat and humidity in this  jungle. This is no place for riding a horse.
Talaya hears there are old Imperial tunnels running underground in this part of Valenwood.nnWhat if this one designed a course down there? Just think of it!
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Shh! You hear that? Sorry. No time for slaptongue now! nnTalaya must be cautious. These Wood Orcs are not happy that this one designed a race course to run right through their lands.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Talaya was raised in these partsjust along the edge of Valenwood. This one has always dreamed of returning and designing a course here.nnPraise the Moons for making it so. This is my finest work.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
This is a harsh land, and it warrants a harsh course. Talaya must warn you, if you decide to race the course, you do so at your own risk. This one cannot guarantee your safety.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
You will not beat my challenge this time. Not unless you are very, very lucky.nnNot even angry Reachmen could stop Talaya from finishing her work!
There is nothing better than riding into battle and killing Reachmen. Perhaps that's why I keep missing the course markers.
Talaya has braved plague and screaming cultists to bring you this course.
It's not the terrain itself that's difficult. It is the wild things along the way, always trying to knock you off your mount.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
This one would appreciate if Ahmat would stop to say "thank you" every now and again.nnIt's not that Talaya craves recognition. Just love.
Don't worry about me. I'm fine. I heard Talaya mention bloodfiends. I am just gathering my courage.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Wet fur, lizard-men, assassins, pirates. Nothing stops Talaya.
I didn't get past the first course marker before I got lost. I guess I'll never win a race.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
The Dark Elves sometimes keep Khajiit and Argonians as slaves. I would prefer not to be here, but I cannot leave Ahmat. He would not know how to take care of himself.
For once my horse did not fail me. But I could not take the dust. I thought I would choke on ash.
The inspector checked my cargo already. There were no problems!
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Do not worry about me. It is nothing. This one simply climbed a tree and could not get down without falling. Very embarrassing.
They say this is an easy course. I'll probably fail. Again.
He's back. Talk to Eupherus, before he gets suspicious. I want to see what he's got in store for you.
Hurry, head down into the cellars. I'll keep watch here. Over this ale.
What'd you think of the speech? Not bad, I hope.
Would have been nice to see the key up there instead of me preaching.
It doesn't surprise me that we failed, although I admit, I did believe we were going to do it at one point.
Least Nicolas is taking over. He's a much better leader.
Pardon me.
Headman Cosh is just up the steps. I'd hurry if I were you. Wouldn't want to disappoint at initiation.

Satakal's coils surround you, friend. My remaining acolytes are much more attentive, and the Scaled Court no longer seeks to steal what is mine. We have shown the power of the one true serpent, and those who reject him suffer his fangs. nnThank you.
You should not be here, walker. The moons have told Thalinfar so.
Have you rescued our guards yet? Please, get back out there and try to find them.
Have  have you done it, Milksop?nnDid you put that spirit down?
You're actually going in there, aren't you? Do you have a death wish?nnThe Celestial Serpent himself leads the Scaled Court in these caverns!

I overheard your talk with the Khajiit. I can't believe he convinced you to enter these caverns. We've been trying to get him to leave.nnThe Celestial Serpent stalks these caves, and he has plans for Craglorn. For all of Tamriel.
How  how have you returned? The master should have  what have you done? What have you done to the master?
Lashburr can't wait to see Agganor's mounted helm! Not a head covering fit for an Iron Orc, but good to befoul.nnBut Lashburr has said too much. Walk away, little goat. Walk away.
Hope you're feeling good after that latest job. Disputes aside, you've proven yourself to be a very capable assassin.
You're lucky the tenets and their threats hold little weight these days. I suppose the guild has grown corrupt enough with their excess that this will go by unnoticed.
Greetings.
Please take my offer. My word is good, I swear it! I'm not sure who I must have wronged to deserve this, but I can and will repay you if you let me live.
Never seen you around here before. New to the Dale?
I hate making supper decisions. I wish my husband would just decide for once.
It's about time I hit the tavern. Been quite a day so far.
Lovely day isn't it? I hope it remains nice tonight.
Spare a coin for a poor soul?
Have you seen a cat around? An orange tabby?
Look at those guards. I remmeber back when Margrette had her doors open to everyone.
Fishin's been pretty good lately. Should get a good market price on these. Not to mention a decent meal out of Sara.
Haven't seen your face around here, stranger. What brings you to Wolfbane Dale?
Good luck with the job.
All right. You've sprung me from prison. Now let's get out of here. We've got spellplates to steal.
The Dominion still hasn't found the keystone, you should still be able to swipe it under their nose.
Why is the Pact here? Have my friends all died? Hurry and free me, if that's why you've come.
You're the one I called, right? The assassin?
Get into the fortress, open the gate for us. There should be a lever at the top of the tower.nnVarn will find you inside, I'll be in charge of making sure no one leaves these docks alive.
You're pretty good. We swept through here like a dark wind.nnI'm going to get this lock open, then you're going to take the next task.
Heard you speaking to Turuk. If you're going into those caves, you're going to need equipment.nnJust so happens I have some to part with. What do you say? Give me your money.

Did I hear that right? You're going into those caverns?nnWe're in no shape to do it, so you might as well. But you'll need some potent soul gems to take those cultists on. Lucky for you, I have a few lying around.
Welcome, initiate. I have a job for you.
Go stand with the others below. Don't want to make it obvious who I appointed.
I suppose some large changes are going to be in order after today.
Oosh and I will be discussing this at length. There's definitely something more than the Listener wanting to enforce the tenets going on here.
Wait, wait. I don't want to miss this!
Hmph. We came down here to get away from the filthy ears of island rats. And yet, here you are. nnWhat do you want?
You again.
Ah, look who we have here.

It must have been gruesome work, but thanks again for dealing with the Scaled Court in Skyreach Hold. I'm sure you saved many lives.nnI only hope the Scaled Court doesn't return to try again. That would be disastrous.
I hope you slept well, my friend. I apologize for the slight inconvenience. But we have plans for you.
We have been watching it work. We have seen it kill. We saw the joy in its eyes as it took an innocent life. We took it to a safe place. We want to test it.

You return. Before you say anything, I want to restate what I said earlier. I've devoted my life to the Night Mother, Sithis, and the Dark Brotherhood. I hold no ill will against you. I cannot control the contracts we receive, only see them through.
I'm embarrassed to say it, but you did what we couldn't. For that, you have my gratitude.
Good work. I hope I get to have some real contracts like you someday.
I can't believe they ate our friends. What kind of monsters would do something like that? I mean, other than Iron Orcs and trolls, that is.
Better to know what happened than never know for sure, right? That's what Camaarie always said.nnI miss her so much.
Impressive. You're still alive.
It looks confused to see us.

As soon as I heal up, I'm going back out there. We've got a score to settle and I need to chop up a few dozen Iron Orcs.nnBut thanks for taking care of the Butcher. I'm pretty sure he'd have killed me without working up a sweat.
Ah, you're the one I've been waiting for.
The wamasu den is next on Veesk's list. I think that's where we need to go.nnWe should hurry. I've got a strange feeling about all this.
There are few things I hate more than Clannfear. Make it quick, but don't skimp on the pain, all right?
I approve of your choice. Varn will make an excellent Listener.nnI will bring you back to Void's Embrace. Are you ready?
Had you chosen me, I would have said to pick Oosh instead. I approve.nnShall we leave this place, and return to Void's Embrace?
You've got to help me! By the Eightthe pain!
Hope the mission is going well. Seems an interesting place to kill a man  at a funeral.
By the Eight, I already said I didn't want to fight!

So that's how he did it! He was imbuing the trolls with pure nirncrux! Fusing the armor and the runes into a powerful whole!nnI wonder what would happen if one of the mortal races was subjected to the process?
Hey  have you heard the one about the Orc Chief and the pumpkin patch? No? Heydon't gimme that look! I've got lots of Orc friends!
You are a shining light in the darkness, friend. Yes. You definitely have a divine glow about you. nnI trust you were able to recover some of the statue fragments?
You're finally here. So is the Celestial Serpentyou'll find him through those doors.nnBe careful.
None of these deaths would have been necessary if the Serpent hadn't lied to me.

Blessings of the Divines upon you. I will not forget the selfless aid you have given todayand at no small risk to yourself. nnShould the time come when that dread creature stirs again, we will be ready. Until then, safe journey to you.
Not now! I want to watch this.
I sense Cassipia's presence, but I do not see her. Be on your guard.

I'm impressed. You demonstrated a willingness to risk everything for the sake of others. You even helped someone you once called an enemy.nnMaybe this world isn't as irredeemable as I imagined. Thank you for helping me correct this terrible mistake.

This workspace is appalling! Instruments clogged with haywhat in Tamriel is . Oh, you're still here. nnHave you already gathered the information I requested? What alacrity! Did I give you a haste potion? No, I would remember that.
Hah, I knew you'd come back alive. No poncy Elven High Kinlord fancydress mageling was going to stop the likes of you.
Trees grow rings as you wait, Undaunted. Don't you want your reward?
You are looking for those Legion Zero saboteurs, yes? Or did you already find them? nnTell Shaghila their blood now mixes with that nasty sewer water.
You here for crafting certification? Don't worry, there's no cost involvedyour alliance covers all my fees.nnOnce you're certified, they'll let you fulfill the crafting writs. Everyone wins!

I have the faintest sense that the Warrior is nearby, but I can't see his face or hear his voice. What's happening to me?nnWill my skills disappear along with my memories? Has the Warrior truly abandoned me? Bah! Leave me to my grief!

I knew I could count on you. I last saw Titus in the north, searching for his wife's grave.nnAs his mind slips away, he fights to hold onto it. It pains him to accept that all he knew is dead and gone, yet he strives to keep the memories alive.
<Blacksmithing writs are posted to this section of the board.>
<Alchemy writs are posted to this section of the board.>
<Clothing writs are posted to this section of the board.>
<Enchanting writs are posted to this section of the board.>
<Provisioning writs are posted to this section of the board.>
<Woodworking writs are posted to this section of the board.>
You're here for crafting certification, yes? Fear not, your alliance covers my considerable fees.nnIf you can prove your basic competence, I'll certify you so you may fulfill crafting writs.
Zantan has been inspired by your five-clawed nature! Your very presence gives him strength! So go! The Wood Elves will need you again before this ordeal is over!
I'm going to be all right. I'm sure the others are in dire straits.

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"King Jorunn extends an invitation! Master crafters await you in <<1>>! They offer free training for those new to a craft, and free certification for accomplished crafters!"
"All members of the Ebonheart Pact! Master crafters await you in <<1>>. They offer free training for those new to a craft, and free certification for accomplished crafters!"
I think I'm going to be fine. The others will need you. I didn't think it would be like this. None of us did.
Go! I've seen what you can do.nnIf someone has a fighting chance against the Valkyn, it's you! You wanted a way out? Slay him, and you'll get one!
Go! You'll do more good clearing the path for me.nnI'll be back to cutting in a moment. Just like weeding my garden.

Brittgerd is finished with the Undaunted. With Hogondar. She will have trouble forgetting this trip to Oblivion. Perhaps I will join herfind a quiet corner of Skyrim and become a farmer.nnHa! She wishes! Undaunted! Undaunted! I am Undaunted!
I will be fine in a moment. Hogondar can fall on his sword if he gets bored.
Go! Sobabe promises to hurry. It is in her best interest.
I erect the spine of .nnI erect  I don't feel so good.
I'm good. Give me a moment, and I'll be right along.nnNo, really. Stop staring.
I'll be all right.nnHaven't had this much fun since I fought in the war.

This one cannot thank you enough for returning Rabe-ma. Such things hold so many sweet memories. Days with my sisters dancing in the sun! Mother's moon sugar brittle! nnThey are gone but not forgotten, as long as Rabe-ma remains.
Welcome to the enclave. Speak to Maj al-Ragath if you have come about the pledge.
First my parents, then my sister. Now it's my turn, I suppose.
You made us proud today.

Rayzeeh sent word that you captured the Nobles District. Those are the best tidings I've heard all week. nnNow I just need to figure out how to move this command center up there. Anything to get out of these sewers.
Keep your head down. I don't want to lose another bounty because of your clumsiness.
Blood and steel, warrior. Did you come from the sewers? nnI hope you don't mind me asking, did you see a vampire down there? I am sad to say  he is my clan brother  or was.
Do you have the crown? Let me see that. Quickly!

Stay back, you! I'll bring the full fury of Julianos down on your head if you . Oh wait, you're not one of them! I'm sorry, just a bit jumpy, and my eyes aren't what they were.nnWhat brings you all the way up here?

You see me not at my best, wayfarer. I just needed a rest. My friends and I were discovered by these creatures. The Daedra are everywhere down here.nnI've taken shelter here, but I don't know how long this respite will last.
Kireth really ought to know better than to jump into strange holes. She knows my nerves can't handle it.
Most of the dwemer constructs in this ruin are heavily corroded. We need to find a centurion coresomething that's been protected from the elementsto get a good sample of this unusual metal.

I wish I could tell you the best way to get into the fort, but we have three different clans here, and every chief claims they're on the verge of breaking through.nnTalk to the clan chiefs. Maybe you can get a sense of what works best for you.
They told me it was cold up here in Wrothgar, but I thought they exaggerated.nnI imagined it would be like the desert at night, but I was wrong. I could not have imagined a cold such as this.
Arushna here has been generous enough to capture this durzog for me to tame. Did you find the whistle?
Ah! It is excellent to see you again. Tell medo you have the egg? Do you have my frozen egg?

Maybe there's hope after all. Look for my first mate Elvira out there too. If you can save them, that's something. nnOf course, I still lost my ship  and S'rashi put up gold for this venture. He's gonna feed my beef-witted arse to the horkers!
I can already feel the air beginning to change. Thank you.
The fool thinks he can tame a durzog. He can do what he likes, as long as he pays.

Hm. I don't see an old crazy-looking Redguard Siege Engineer hobbling along behind you, so I'm guessing this you bring dark tidings. nnIf that's the case, just tell me you got the schematics. Otherwise, this entire voyage was a loss.
Please hurry. If you are going to insist on saving my life, you must at least try to go quickly. My schematics are all that really matters.
Oh, excellent. The Orcs did not eat you, as I'd feared. Did you find anything of interest?
Could you talk some sense into this Orc? I'm frankly a bit busy to deal with his second thoughts.

I'll be a Bosmer's arse. King Jorunn said you'd pass this way, but I thought it was just horker-dung.nnI hear you've killed more people than the Knahaten Flu. I don't know thoughyou really think you're tough enough for the mountains of Wrothgar?
Go on then. No dawdling about. You have Reachmen to kill. nnI know my son's itching to get started. You two enjoy yourselves now!
May Trinimac's light guide your path, my friend  always.

Damn it's nice out here, isn't it? The stench of those Reachmen was nauseating. nnNothing like some fresh Wrothgarian air and the satisfaction of knowing Mogbach's dead and we're alive. I'm glad it's not the other way around!
I don't believe what I'm hearing. He knew there was a Dwemer ruin under our quarry, and now, to make it up to us, he wants to use those things to help rebuild Orsinium?
I hope you have those samples. The alchemists are driving me crazy asking for some.
I hope your return is a good sign. I have been hesitant to send any soldiers out into the sewers while I know those saboteurs are active.nnTell me, did you find those dogs and put them down?
Can you believe it? A female chieftain! We'll be the laughingstock of Wrothgar! I've known Ushruka since she was a babe. Fine woman, but she won't last long with everyone scrambling for her head.

Good day, friend. Or is it evening? So hard to tell down here. Hm. Even in this dim light, your face looks familiar. Yes. Stormhaven. You were the one with the Stonechewers' totem.nnAnd now you're here killing riekr. Is this really necessary though?
Ushruka will be the harbinger of a new era among the Orcs, and Orsinium will be the better for it.

I'm sorry. Do you need something? If not, go bother someone else. nnIf I don't finish all these texts within the week, my master will send me out into the field where I'll probably get killed. I prefer the books.
Leave me alone, outsider. We've got enough trouble as it is.
You did it. You made it into Oozrul's tomb, didn't you? nnDid you find the helm? Did you find "Slime Spiller"?
If that damned Moth Priest doesn't get moving soon, I'll move through her.nnGet going. Maybe she'll follow. We need to retake the throne room, first and foremost.
<This is a shrine to Malacath.>

Welcome back to Orsinium. Glad I finally found you. King Kurog wanted me to extend a formal invitation to come and meet him in the throne room. nnHe said you were a trustworthy ally before, and that he needs you just as much now as he did then.
I had no light left. You are my light now. You've shown me that there is hope. nnI will stay here and finish mourning my sister. When I'm done? We'll see.
I had no light left. You are my light now. You've shown me that there is hope. nnI will stay here and finish mourning my sister. When I'm done? We'll see.
I had no light left. You are my light now. You've shown me that there is hope. nnI will stay here and finish mourning my sister. When I'm done? We'll see.

By the way  you picked the perfect moment to put the Ice Heart on the table. I thought Chief Bazrag's eyes would fall out of his head. Heh.nnYes. You've proven to be the perfect ally to my son. Now we must see to the priestess.
So Ushruka, in the guise of her brother Ulghesh, won the right to be called "Chief"? Huh.
Herding complete.
Reality is bending around us. The pinnacle of the White-Gold Tower is straight ahead, through that portal.nnThat's where you'll find Clivia.
The now full crate sits here, waiting for you to sign the shipment manifest
Smashing Daedra with an axe is one of my favorite past-times. Do you need something?
I took one bad scratch to the face and now look at mestuck here handing out rewards to other soldiers.nnLet me guessyou want a reward for something?
Don't ever volunteer for quartermaster duties. In fact, don't ever volunteer for anything in this army. That's the best advice you'll get all day.nnSo, how can I help you?
<A new bounty notice has been posted to the Hunting Board.>
Is it done? Did you manage to disrupt the ritual once again?
Aishah is happy to see you again, Walker. You have been busy, yes?nnYou rescued the people as this one asked?
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX
YOU ARE GOING TO SHUT THAT MAW
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX
YOU SHUT THE MAW. NOW YOU GET THE BOX.nnBOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX BOX

Come stretch your tail by my fire, fellow Lukiul. As the stones of this city grow colder, we must rely on each other if we are to survive.nnYou've been outside. Tell me, have the chains already pulled us into Coldharbour?
Thank you so much for agreeing to help. Oh, I hope they're all right.
Yes, this will be close enough, I think. Are you prepared?
This one is relaxing. Can you not see this? Please, just go away.
Astia is anxious to study that blood. Have you retrieved it?
I was afraid something like this was going to happen. Poor Nadafa! She loved to go walking in the dead of night. She said it helped her sleep .

I'm sorry if I look disappointed. When you came in, I thought you were someone else.nnI'm terribly worried about my house-servant, Gryna. My husband passed away years ago, and we never had children, so she's all I have left.
Hello.
Hello.

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"King Jorunn extends an invitation! Master crafters await you in <<1>>! They offer free training for those new to a craft, and free certification for accomplished crafters!"
You did it! I wasn't sure you had it in you.
I have no idea how you got this far, but go no farther. Soon, we battle to retake the Palace in the name of the Empress Regent.
Stand where we can see you.
This is no place for dawdling. Move along. Preferably back the way you came.
So you managed to survive. You've done some fighting before. I can tell.
I'm not following you. I'm allowing you to lead me.
Quickly, take the side tunnel to return to the entrance!
I have received word from the Fighters Guild that you signaled triumph in the Market District. I am glad to hear it. Victory is a slippery fish, but we cast a wide and terrible net.
Don't you have Daedra to slay? I have nothing to say to enemies of the Pact.

You're back? Don't get me wrong, I heard you signaled victory in the Arboretum and I'm grateful, but I can't imagine what in Oblivion brought you down here again. nnIf I didn't have to be here, I wouldn't. This place is disgusting.
You must have sharp claws to stalk these streets, walker. This one prefers to remain in the shadows. nnAll the activities Pudazi enjoysthey are done in the shadows.
Ha! I know that look. That's your "I just pounded the piss out of a whole mess of saboteurs" face! Am I wrong?
You've proven yourself worthy champion. I'm impressed.
Ew! You've got bits of that barrel-belly's fleshiness all over you. That makes even the Rat's stomach turn, and he eats in the sewers.nnSo you killed this barrel-belly yourself?
You are the one sent by the sewer-dwelling Ebonheart Pact, yes? Why you choose to live in a stinking dung-hole is beyond me. nnBut Ezudash digresses! Let's discuss these anchors, yes?

General Aklash sent you? All right. Let me make one thing clear then. I owe no loyalty to the Covenant. My duty is to the Fighters Guild. nnI will avail you of my knowledge of the anchors  but only so that we can save the city.

Well, I guess you've gone and proven skeevers can fly  I hate to say it, but if I was a gambling woman, I'd have bet against you.nnWhen I heard that horn, I nearly soiled myself. I didn't, of course, but I was pretty surprised.
Look, if you get killed out there, don't blame me, because I was just joking. nnI don't want people going around saying Jagar got someone killed, because it really  it won't be my fault.
That was quite a feat you pulled off out there. To be honest, I'm humbled that you went to such lengths on my behalf.
Back again. Had some more time to think about joining the Enforcers? You won't regret it. It's the one way you can get paid to start a tavern brawl.
I'd encourage you to mend your ways outlaw. Your crimes are well-known here and will not be tolerated. But there is still hope, you can cast aside wickedness and take up the mantle of the Enforcers.

As I feared, we arrived in different locations. I am in a place with the smell of burning ash on a hot wind and the sounds of a distant battle. nnIt matters not. You have awakened once again and we must set you on your path.
We are blessed with the presence of one such as you.
That was so insulting. Julien is clearly not suitable material for a woman of my station.
It seems I am doomed to admire Guen from afar. nnPerhaps after a few years of experience in the High King's army, she will reconsider and give me a chance.
Thank you for your help with the Glass Shipment.  Jerall was pleased.
We are in your debt for helping with this accursed plague.
Finally, a wolf in sheep's clothing.
I'd be surprised if the people I sent you to talk to agreed on anything. How did it go?
Jacinta send you, did she? Fine. I suppose I'll hear you out.
Thanks for taking care of those wolves. It gives me more time to take care of this village.
Thank you for your help. There's something I must speak with you about, but it can wait until your business with the King has concluded.
Have you completed the task I set before you?
Our fate, Camlorn's fate, is in your hands. Fight well!
I... I don't know what to do. I suppose there's no doubt now.
We've got work to do, but between the two of us, we'll bring those children home.
You have... potential.
When you've proven yourself a true ally of Camlorn, I'll give you the chalice. Not a moment before.
You come at Oron's behest? Then you are on the king's business. I'll help however I can.
Excellent. You look to be in fine health, so we should begin at once.
You help me, I help you. Return when you've done what I asked.
I can't thank you enough for killing Necanis. We can handle the rest of the rabble ourselves. You are always welcome here.
Look for Thetis south of Grayborne. His house is midway between here and the lake.
We heard about you fighting the undead! We aspire to your heights.
We've heard about you driving back the undead. Impressive.
The Bloody Eye are not a simple group of mystics, stranger. We direct our vision into more than just the simple physical realm of flesh that we stand in now. We are guardians of the Veil.
Do not worry for my companions. They will take care of things on their end. We have our own duties we must attend to.
In order to push out the darkness of this land, we ourselves must become part of it.
They think you are the one? Heh, let us see if your spirit is not simply ripped to shreds.
These are dark times. Even Tamarus is showing signs of the madness! He wants help from those who would practice the dark arts. There's a reason why those mystics hide in the mountains!
It is done.. We've struck a blow to Coldun that will set them back a good time.. but they will return with a force that we will not be able to stop...
Our failure has unleashed spirits of anger and torment, who menace Camlorn. We must stop them!
When you've completed your patrol, we'll speak again.
I fear the undead will haunt Northmoor forever.
I hope the holy water fulfilled its purpose.
Together, we will stop this evil.
Slowly, the nightmares of Silvermist shrink back. You are a force to be reckoned with, friend.
I am glad to see that even in these dark times, High Rock still has heroes. What is your concern?
I'm glad the matter we discussed has been, er, dealt with. nnRest assured, the Duke of Camlorn does not forget his friends.
Let me know which potions work and which don't... and be careful. I haven't finished testing those yet.
Being raised as undead is horrible, but I worry that the Blackhand's plans are far worse.
At least now we know what we're facing. nnMeanwhile, Gloria has discovered something important about how Faolchu came to power.
The Unusual Thorn that you found reeks of magic.
Ah, back with Shava's roots; you are a good and useful assistant to Shava!
May you never feel this pain, my friend. Even love is not worth the price of eternal torment.
We'll handle the rest, and we'll help Camlorn rebuild. I'm certain you now face bigger challenges.
One less nuisance to deal with... and one step closer to retaking Camlorn. When these cursed werewolves are all in the ground, the first round is on me.
You've done quite a service for Deleyn's Mill, <<1>>. Thank you.
My sister must have tried to banish the corruption on her own. Where she failed, we must succeed.
Had any luck finding harpy feathers?
Well met, my fellow adventurer! You are an adventurer, right?
Present the wyrd offering in the center of our ritual site. Stand between the five standing stones. I pray the spirits will listen.
I have no right to ask more of you, but... would you do us one last favor?
The spirits chose you as their champion. Once they chose me, as well.nnNow we must work together to restore the land's purity.
Ormax expects us to make up for all our lost time.
At least we have our health and work to do, eh?
Ormax wants us to double our efforts.
Thanks to you, we can all get back to work. A blessing an a curse, to be sure. nnStill, you have my thanks.
Look, I gave you the money. I don't know what more you could want from me. nnYou should leave before someone gets suspicious.
Vartisan Ameralee must have a solution to our dilemma. Pray speak with her at once, Numinous.
Felicitous greetings, and welcome to the Kinhouse of the Felballin!
Place the Sload Lure on the Sun Column found on the furthest island to the southwest.
The Elementals' work was not to be interrupted, but such is the folly of the Maormer. Please return their Piths using the Fissures.
Would you mind standing back ? You are rather filthy.
You have already recovered the Varla Lens and Hainen's book? My, you have been busy while I was... detained. May I see them, please?
You have done us a great service. Yet more remains, if we are to restore the Varlines of Isque.
Isque Roses grow along the river, just to the northeast.
Those foul witches shall be purged from these shores. By the Fugue of Arbis, I swear it so.
By the sound of it I divine you have found us a Blessed Bell.
Ah, you have returned. I take it you repulsed the Zombies?
Not even werewolves can stand against us for long.
Have you collected Fire Salts from the Incendiaries?
What is that rattling noise?
Have you checked on my soul gem?
I'd follow Magus Commander Danain into Oblivion itself.
Truly, you have much to teach us, Numinous.
I appreciate your help. With the wounded coming and going, every ally who can help is a blessing from the Divines!

Apothecaries like myself write down only useful cures. You can rub a stone on a wart during the waning moon, then bury the stone to cure your warts. And then there's...what's that? Foxglove Nectar. Oh! Of course!
The shriek of Stormwitches confirms your success.
So Blain tracked me. I wish I could thank him for not turning me in. You must not think very highly of me, deserting as I did.
The champion of Auri-El returns. Honor and praise, Numinous.
I defer to your wisdom, Optimate. May your travels be blessed.
Would you favor us by playing the Sacred Instrument near at hand? Be not bashful.
It is time for Nirn to brighten our sky once again.
You have my thanks, Optimate.
You must enlist the aid of the Exemplars at the Shrines around The Orrery. Only then can we know what threat we face.
Poor Vilmo, blind to the truth which I have seen. He must be enlightened.
What news have you of Skyharker Suuniqwe?
There's no time to waste. We have to reactivate the Midnight Talisman before Angof can react.
Have you found the book yet? It must have fallen somewhere below. I pray it did not fall in the water!
With the power of the Midnight Talisman, we may finally be able to strike at Angof directly. Let's not tarry.
With the Varla Lens missing, the lines of power connecting this Kinship to the Orrery have gone down. Were the Varlines to be restored, I could transport you to the Orrery swiftly and safely.
It is good to be whole again. I thank you for this.
I cannot leave Ackers, but please, help my friends. I'll tend the nightblade's wounds.
You've given me peace of mind at last.nnI will always mourn the loss of my son, but knowing that he died well fills me with pride.
Now that we have the Midnight Talisman, it's time to reactivate it. We'll need your help.
Cursed cats! All my rats were gone in moments. What a dervish of destruction!nnI hope for your sake, friend, that you had nothing to do with this.
Speak to Langdruun within the Kinhouse. He will be expecting you.
I trust your call upon the Battlereeve went well. If you will excuse me, I have orders to attend. Fortune favor thee, Numinous.
Al'kari is pleased to see you again, hero of chickens.
The Gem Spiders can be found in the rear of the Menagerie to the north.
What's your business here?
Hurry to Crosswych, <<1>>. Old Man Murell's going to want to meet you
May the Ascendants watch over you, Numinous.
That will be all, my young Numinous.
The best place to find a brush pile would be the cliffs northwest of here. Be on your guard.
Trade is the lifeblood of these isles. Those who yet say it is magic are simply envious.
Despite the failing of the Varlines and the rise of Orgnavar, trade yet flows through Orrery.
With the Varlines awry, our own magic books are a danger to us. I fear my mother was attacked.
I have inspected the Orc skull.
Glory is to be won on the beaches. Yet here I stand, barring the door.nnI am told it is an honorable duty.
The Syldarim of The Orrery have sent an Emissary bearing a message of unity. I am grateful for your deeds, Numinous.
Back for more, <<1>>? Fortunately the Maormer have deserted this site, now that the Welkynd Stone is safely back in our hands.
Perhaps we could speak some other time, Optimate.
There are many wounded soldiers I must tend to.
Please, you can't take my husband. I know he's sorry for what he did.

I miss my friend. I know you did what you felt was right, but all the same, perhaps you should have let Moreau be.nnMy ring is still missing, the real thief remains at large, and a man who made a mistake is in prison.
Come you with passion in your heart? Sweet words on your lips?
Need to go. Have to go. Stars flying by. Wind in my mane. Bored here.
I hope you gave that despicable thief a fitting punishment for his crime.
You stand at the gates of The Orrery, Optimate.
Could I break my bond with my model planet, I would have left the Orrery already.
Praise and honor to you, Optimate!
Sir Hughes has turned himself in, and Alcaire is in your debt. nnI have one last request of you.
If you're here for a drink, talk to Ruhamza... if he has any ale left.

Everyone's gone mad! I've been praying that you don't suffer from this affliction, <<1>>.nnThe fear, the pain, the uncertainty... they're the real enemies, aren't they? nnThe darkness is coming to engulf us all.
They're out to get her. nnI've got to protect her reputation. nnShe's my friend. Dabienne would do the same for me, wouldn't she?

This whole thing was like some terrible nightmare. It reminds me of the day I lost my husband so many years ago.nnI don't know if you can understand. I've moved on, but sometimes, I still feel a little lonely.
There's a few less Daedra in the world now, I bet. What have you collected?
<<1>> will meet you at the entrance to the mews.nnBe swift. We know not how much longer Lord Montclair will keep his prisoners alive.

As much as I want to rush out and put <<1>>'s head on a pike, I have a responsibility to these people.nnJonah is a strange one, but I doubt he can fend for himself, let alone protect his mother. I hope you can find them quickly.
So we meet again. Did Calden send you, or is this concerning another matter?
You bring warning from Fahjiri? I'll have words with that cat - she has more to do with this than she admits. Your warning comes late. Look in on Durak, then return to me.

I wonder what Duke Nathaniel might gain from the murder of the duchess....nnNobles are never above advancing their position through monstrous acts.nnOf course, I'm just a courtier. What would I know of such things?
The memories of my fallen comrades rest in the walls of this hall. Those memories will give me strength in the coming fight.nnI'm ready to face the forces threatening us.
I've seen to the captives. You've done good work here.nnTime will tell if Lady Eselde can protect them from Lord Montclair, and themselves.
We must destroy the corrupted nereids!

Just back from the docks, are you? nnThe Midnight Swell used to be a safe ship, back when Captain Lash was the captain. nnNo doubt its new captain threw the old one overboard. Fed him to the water Dreugh, I bet. nnYou'd best be wary near that lot.
You've saved our family, <<1>>, when no one else would help us.nnWe can't trust anyone but you.
You've defeated the evil that caused us so much suffering, but I still have to endure his curse.nnI tried to save these people. Why am I the one who's being punished?
The Orcs use anchors to keep this shield in place. nnThey've scattered them about the ruins, and they guard them closely.
Watch your step here, stranger. I've got an eye on you.
The Divines will not forget what you've done for an innocent. Neither will I.
All's quiet on my watch. Thank the Divines for small blessings.
My brother is beside me again. We are together in death, as we were in life.
I dread the prospect of having to do battle with my fellow knights. nnNonetheless, it must be done. I've ordered the knights who have joined our cause to take up strategic positions around the keep.
<<1>> is gone! I can't find her anywhere in the camp.nnShe shouldn't be moving about with her injuries. If you find her, please let me know.
Verandis trusts you. Hopefully, you now see that not all vampires are evil.
If you want my respect, draw some blood in my arena! nnI don't care whether you slaughter your enemy, only that you fight with honor!
If you need something, talk to the Constable. Leave me in peace.
You've proven very resourceful. As promised, I can help you restore Makana's memory to repay Durak for sharing his Sleepless Potion with me.
We have dreamed a nightmare together, and come out alive. I am glad to see you awake, as well.
If the wailing keeps up, we may find ourselves without any visitors at all. nnIf I had a choice, I'd leave as well!

If you've come to poke fun at the prisoner, you'd better think twice. I'll be out of these stocks soon, and then you'll have to watch your back.nnThey may not have enough evidence to hold me, but that doesn't mean I'm not a dangerous criminal.
Did you see her? Wearing the necklace I made? Well, I hope you're happy. This is all your fault.nnNow go away and let me work in peace.
So you live, and Lord Montclair does not. Things could not have gone better, I'd say.nnI'm sure your noble house will be glad to hear of Montclair's death, though their strife is far from over.
Go as fast as you can, Lieutenant. Until we've tried this, the king won't even talk about surrender.nnWe have to get him to come around before it's too late.

Oh no! It's you. Have you come from Hosni? Please. Please have mercy.  nnS'rashi promises to have Hosni's gold soon, but S'rashi cannot get Hosni's gold if he's dead. Tell S'rashi you've not come to kill him.
You. You're to go right in.
If I see you, I'm supposed to send you in. So I'm sending you in.
You've returned, my friend, and you look well! Much better than the last hero I sent to retrieve a wyvern egg.

You'll find the ward somewhere inside the Plane Merge, <<1>>.nnBe careful in there. We've already lost a scouting party, and I haven't a clue what got them. I'm sure it's waiting eagerly for more victims.
Whoever did this to Mathias needs to pay. Hope you figure out who it was. I bet it was that creepy Altmer, Yarelion. nnI suppose it could have been any of the suitors though.
The blue stone is called azurite. It's like her, when she speaks in my head. Her voice is soft. Do you hear it?nnTake my pickaxe. Find the blue stone. Bear caves. North. Near caves. You must.
Do you have it? Quickly! I think she's getting worse!
We've all been damned by the tragedies at Crestshade. nnI've... come to terms with that.
My mistress Azura offers advice that will aid Gavaudon against the Omen of Counting Stars.nnIt can only be defeated in Vaermina's realm of dreams and nightmares.
Good luck. You'll need it.
One has accomplished what many could not.nnRivenspire can now begin again.
I don't know about everyone else but I don't think Borkul is any better of a leader than Godrun.
Traveller! Could you offer any aid to <<1>>?
Hosni has ruined me! Rebuilding what he's stolen will take years.nnI have no further use for you. Get out of my sight!
Have you acquired any samples of tainted flesh?  Any of the those harpies will do.nnThey're right there ... emanating.
Go on into the tower and talk to the Hinaults. Reassure them. They're both pretty shaken up.nnBut if Heloise doesn't return soon, I may need to send you out to find her.
The Swamp Cypress creaks.
We failed to save Crestshade, but perhaps there is hope for Rivenspire.
You know, I didn't really think about what I'd do with all these thumbs.nnSay, would you like a necklace?
Misfortune hangs over Rivenspire like a dark cloud, friend. And it doesn't help that the city leaders can't agree on which way is up.
Travel to the east, into the Bonebarrow, and speak to Golleon. He will need your help.

Well, I can hardly believe what I've heard. If this artifact of evil has been destroyed, when will its minions dissipate?nnI know I am too impatient. I do not know how you did this, but the fact that you did is enough of a reason to celebrate.
How did those Saproot Shoots work out? I bet you made a right mess for those ugly Imperials.
Take that charm I gave you to Priestess Fleile.nnShe's in Razorvine Refuge, north of here. nnTell her of your success. She will be pleased.
I'm not sure I can stand much more of this. The bodies  the blood .nnI wanted to save this family, but look what happened. It feels like everything has suddenly gone wrong.

If I could trade my life to bring back my dear Lakana, I would. Moving on will not be easy, but I must honor her sacrifice by doing all that I can to protect the Covenant.nnI will speak with King Fahara'jad. Perhaps we can come together in mourning.
What did you find? Did she take anything else from the Barrows?
Go on, take a good look around. Don't be shy, my dear. I certainly won't be! I have nothing to hide.
If Alcaire is truly threatened, regardless of where it comes from, I will defend it to the death.
Don't be so quick to leave.
Bring me good news, <<1>>, or bring me nothing at all.
Christophe was a fool, but I'm overjoyed to see him alive. My nephew and I owe your our freedom. We won't forget.
Thank you for giving me back my memory. If only Rin and I had gone to Ahtah in the first place... but you cannot unswing a sword.
Find Sorcassil, but go with caution. None are safe from Gil-Var-Delle's deathly curse.
Forget I said anything about the Honey Incident, all right?
I'm satisfied that Arniel will keep his place. nnPerhaps now I can attend to other matters.
If Alcaire falls, what's next, Wayrest? If these Redguards mean to invade, we have to stop them here.
<<1>>! It's good to see you.
Your handling of the Fellwatch situation was truly impressive.nnYou have a promising future as a lawman, if that's what you want.
I'd go give Normar a piece of my mind, but he said if he saw me again, he'd call the guards.nnWhat kind of man won't listen to his own citizens?
Has Haven fallen to the Imperials?
I saw the glyph on table with some soul gems. There was a mage guarding it, however.

I knew when I first met you that you would be the one. Well, perhaps not right away. I've been wrong before, mind you, but I was fairly confident.nnLet's finish this. It would be a shame to perish before the conclusion of all of this, wouldn't it?

I'd do anything for Leah! I'd slay a Daedric prince barehanded for her.nnI'd climb a mountain to gather the rarest flowers!nnI'd run through the streets naked, screaming her name and proclaiming my love for her!nnShe must know: I'd do anything!
Hopefully with a bit of rest, Tristan will be as good as new. nnOnce he's recovered, I can finally return to my research on Vampire lore! I can't wait!
Already my people report a sheen in our horses' hides and a spring in their step.nnYou've saved them, <<1>>.
I am badly injured
target: I will need you to deal with the ogres attacking the dam without me.

source: Some of them might not be willing to leave, but it's best they do. Leonce's "empire" won't last forever, and I don't want their blood on my hands.nnBesides, I'm tired of them getting all his attention.
Catian lives in the upper branches of Leaftower. He likes to look down on the "savages."
It appears you've given away all the digging tools.
You can find General Skorsgaard's camp underneath the lighthouse's rocky outcropping.nnI'd suggest traveling north to the lighthouse and taking the footpath down, but it's up to you how to get there.

If you don't mind, please apologize to Mathias for me as well. Tell him I would have him and all the other servants return if they're willing. nnNo more suitors though. I'm done pretending. I have no intention of marrying againcertainly not now.
Duzug is being unreasable. It's not my fault she's lost some cattle!
Please, speak some sense to her. I'm sure the Houses must know of a way to stop this sickness they must!
I've lived here with the giants for a long time. My father fishes with them down on the beach. They're almost like family to us!nnIf you want to speak to them, I can help translate.

If it's mind games they want, they're in for a bittersweet defeat.nnI know Jon is dead. He's not coming back. Whatever that creature is inhabiting his body, it's simply a minion corrupted by dark magicka.nnLight always triumphs over darkness.
We are starving and yet Godrun will not allow us to go resupply.

If it's mind games they want, they're in for a big disappointment.nnI know. Jon's dead. He's not coming back. That creature inhabiting his body is animating it with dark magicka.nnThat means he's a minion of evil, and I will destroy him.
The evil Lich is no more. In time, Gil-Var-Delle will return to Valenwood, starting with Black Log.
If I were older and stronger, I'd set up scarecrows around the village myself, but the elders don't want to lose any more young people. They've forbidden me from going further out.

Oof! Don't mind me. I'm afraid I'm not the man I was in the last war. All those stairs.nnUgh! Can't these beasts ever lair in the middle of a nice, flat plain?nnWe're almost ready to move on the Doomcrag. How is the fighting behind us?
What a patriot of Northpoint you are!nnThe baron is lucky to have such a fine ally.
My friend, have you considered my position in this Nord business? nnI'm sure you can understand my concern for the well-being of Northpoint.
I won't run. I have to face up to what I did.
By Xarxes, that was quite unpleasant! Your aid was timely indeed. I am in your debt, Numinous.
You have a potential cure? Use it on Ameralee, quickly!
You have completed the elixir? Use it on Ameralee. There is only a small chance she will explode.
Fancy a bit of mudcrab to whet your appetite? nnWe'll be eating well tonight, thanks to you!
What shall I do now that the books are all back, you ask? What I always do! I'm going to lounge in my favorite chair with my favorite book.
You were brave for confronting that demon - Isrisa would thank you could she speak.
I assume you will speak for Isrisa, seeing as how I have her voice?
You've had some success with the webs, I think!
Do you require healing?
We have already secured the aid of Isque, <<1>>. I bellieve we must look still farther east, to The Orrery.
Did you use up the poison I gave you? nnHow I wish I could watch them eat that poisoned food....
With the Varla Lens missing, the lines of power connecting this Kinship to the Orrery have gone down. Were the Varlines to be restored, I could transport you to the Orrery swiftly and safely.
Can't a soul just sit and grieve in peace?
This is a sad time for me. Please let me grieve.
Yes? What is it? Probably not as important as what I'm... thinking about doing.
We barely escaped Camlorn with our lives.

I dislike backtracking as much as the next mer, but we have yet to gain the loyalty of High Kinlord Maldarawo of Isque, whose domain lies to the west of here.nnIf you wish, you can go on ahead of me. I will meet you at the Isquer Kinhouse.
It seems our next stop will be among the Skyharkers of The Orrery, <<1>>.nnYou should go on ahead of me. I shall meet you in the Syldarim Kinhouse.

I dislike backtracking as much as the next mer, but we have yet to gain the loyalty of High Kinlord Maldarawo of Isque, whose domain lies to the west of here.nnIf you wish, you can go on ahead of me. I will meet you at the Isquer Kinhouse.
How ever did you manage to overcome so many volatile spiders?

We've seen no signs of Montclair for days, yet his soldiers continue to bolster their ranks.nnMysteries have given way to revelations. If he's sworn his allegiance to vampires, and he's sacrificing his villagers, who knows what power he now holds....
I tire of rumors when what I need are facts. Find me this, and I will count you as my ally. House Tamrith will chafe at the loss of your loyaly, no doubt.
How ever did you manage to overcome so many volatile spiders?
The village has gone completely mad. I'm the only sane one left, if you ask me.nnGo on, talk to the guard. She'll let you in to visit anyone.

Thank Mara, at least I know Govran is still alive.nnThey're killing them, you know. They're aking them out one by one and executing them. I know they are. nnThey say they aren't, but I don't trust them.
Have you dealt with the River Dreugh yet? Nasty things, I hope to be rid of them all one day.
Hurry on to Sal. nnI'm not getting any younger!

It's up to you, at least for the moment. Until I recover, you're the only one who can stop these fake pirates from enslaving Koeglin Village.nnThese Daedra can't fool me! I know the truth about these so-called pirates.
Will Colane Oscent let us unload our cargo? Are we going to get fresh supplies?
Captain Veronika runs a tight ship, but I've never met a nicer Nord.
There is no greater honor than to live as a Knight of the Flame.
I don't know why my mistress wanted to see you. I only know the task at hand.nnPlease, seek her out if you want to learn more. I would not dare speak on her behalf.
If the Dominion didn't take back Southpoint when they did, the Imperials would have been too entrenched to be moved.
We beat the coward Imperials here and will defeat them in the war as well.
Take these orders to <<1>> back in town. nnShe must be made aware of this.

You can hear them at night, whispering about us. I can't sleep! My dreams are all nightmares.nnThat ring will kill the hen anyway. I'd rather have her die swiftly than suffer with that thing inside her.

They've taken her, they've taken my farm, and now they've taken over my mind.nnI can't stop. Daedra will kill me. nnThey're going to get me eventually, but only when I stop looking for them. The moment I lower my guard, I will die.
J'Hriss doesn't care what you've heard. J'Hriss is a legitimate businessman.

Not long after you went up the road, Father headed to the older farmhouse. That's a dangerous area. I don't know what ails him.nnDo you think we're being poisoned? You don't think my sister Ganise is....nnNo, that's madness. She's just a bad cook.

So you managed to convince a couple of these villagers to help out? That's great! You've done more for the Midnight Swell than I ever could.nnI wish my brother would hurry up and get here, though. The longer I wait, the more worried I get.
I cannot chat, I must relay a message to the front.
I think you fail to grasp the enormity of the situation.
Penny for an out-of-work eelmer?
Please make your visit to the Hortator brief. nnHis spirit did not die a peaceful death, and he still needs time to recover.
The cliff racers are thick throughout the fort.  You can't move without finding them.
Will you stay and listen to my tale, friend? nnI have no proof but my words and my present condition, yet I must tell the tale all the same.

Killing my fellow knights to restore order was hard enough, but this matter with Sir Hughes is unthinkable.nnHe's down in the infirmary. I'm told he was raving about killing the duchess before he fell unconscious. I-I don't know what to do.
If you're done dealing with the Penitents, tell Champion Shulki you have assisted her for me.
You should speak to my retainer. And please, do not open any of the packages.
Sera Orvona will speak with you now.
Ahjiivi does not know you. Do not think that we are defenseless, or you will suffer the same fate as our captors.
There's nothing over here. This is a waste of my time.
Already word of your dancing prowess spreads through the hot springs! I must say, you have proven marvelously gracious, my dear.
You have bathed my sword in vengeance.nnTake it now down to the fissure. Destroy the evil Fallen Three.
I've been placing bets for a long time. You'd think I might win more often than not, but sadly, that isn't the case.
Lord Ra'ud still stares at me from across the way.nnWell, he can look all he wants, but he made a big mistake. He'll never be with me now.
The knowledge cost them their lives, but the Jaqspur lost in Thrambles taught us about its greatest danger: the Grahtlord.
We shall have to call you <<1>> the Snake Summoner now!
You look tired. Come. Rest with us.
Reywell's mud baths are renown throughout Stormhaven. You should try them!
That seems to have pleased my lady.nnI, however, am not impressed.
Such needless destruction.... Those vicious Imperials and their leader, General Cruor, should be butchered like livestock!nnA thousand curses upon them! A thousand curses...
The dangers of Valenwood at my back and the murderous Imperials on my horizon. I am between the teeth of a beast.
I haven't a care in the world, and there are all these handsome lads about. nnThis is quite a pleasant way to spend the day!
These baths are renown for their curative properties. nnI don't know what they cure, but I'm sure it's working!
Manifests, shipping records, caravan reports... there's got to be some clues in here.nnWe have to find out where these packages came from and who they're for.
Collecting many interesting items under many moons. nnBringing delight to the Ookvoot tribe! nnAdding to Elder Knonk's collection.

When I think how soon I'll be with my Diane, I am overwhelmed. nnShe has beauty. She has grace. She is passion personified. nnShe told you what she wants, and soon, I'll be whispering to her what I want! nnBy the Eight, what a wonderful day!
Ah, <<1>> it's good to see you again.  How goes things with House Dres?
A moment's rest in Reywell would do you some good. nnImagine what staying here forever would do for you!
I do not forget your help with the Blighted.  What can I do for you in return, Blightbane?
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
Another challenger? Ha! I could slay you with one hand tied behind my back.
The personal congratulations of Hoom. The satisfaction in confounding of the loathsome Wud!

Knowing victory in this contest does not matter to the stranger. nnWill the stranger be generous?nnWill the stranger be giving Wud the treasures so that he can defeat Hoom?nnPromising you the prize. Offering you life-long adoration!
In the weeks before the Imperial invasion, there were rumbling sounds from underground. As they landed, a huge sinkhole opened in the middle of town.nnFoul magic, that. I've never heard of the like.
I swear, the vines on that wall keep trying to grab me. This Bosmer magic is unnatural.nnVines should keep still and be decorative, like a good husband.
Bring me three Hammerdeath Victory Tokens, and the Breastplate of Hammerdeath will be yours.
What are you waiting for? Get back in there!
They are getting closer. Good! I'd love a good fight!

Big news out of Haven, eh? Some kind of necromantic device destroyed? I hope that means we can go home soon.nnThose domesticated slouchbears the Imperials slaughtered outside the city must be ripe with maggots by now!
Once we've gotten back to our ship, we'll send all those pirates down to the bottom of the sea!
Once we've gotten back to our ship, we'll send all those pirates down to the bottom of the sea!
It's going to be a hard season without the thunderbug herd.
You'd better go meet with your contact.  It may be a trap, but then again you may be able to find out something useful.
This is a safe place, hidden from outsiders by the Pact-Magic of our people.
Your load looks much lighter. nnLooks like the deliveries went well.
Do you have the spriggan limbs?
Raising netch isn't easy. nnI need those extra hands if I'm going to recover from this setback. nnThese poachers have thoroughly ruined my farm.
