<<1>> will be very pleased to have Irano out of here.nnNow we have a good chance of reclaiming the Ebonheart Wharf.
It should've been me....
Do not interrupt me.
I heard some Razorvines talking about a town up north that was destroyed by Molag Bal. I think it was called... Gilverdale? Something like that, anyway.
I heard some Razorvines talking about a town up north that was destroyed by Molag Bal. I think it was called... Gilverdale? Something like that, anyway.
It's been ages since I had grilled Khaj- grilled senche-tiger.nnThis alliance with the Dominion can get tossed as far as I'm concerned.
I'd rather be hunting thunderbugs.
Kynareth's blessings, stranger.
I need someone who can follow instructions. Get to Quartermaster Laniar and pick up those shields. Now!
I didn't think you were lazy <<1>>. If you want to advance in the craft you must learn recipes.nnI have a few that you can purchase if you have studied enough.
<<1>>, we begin our journey as master and novice. Are you ready?nnAnd please. Address me as Great Sage.
Thank you for telling me. I know it was hard to say.

If we only found skooma in these samples, that would actually be a relief. Unfortunately, this affliction affects everything. nnI'll need to ask the Iliath Temple for further instructions. The outlook for <<1>> doesn't look good.
My broken leg shouldn't heal this quickly. nnReme sure is something special.
My cold's fading. Thanks to Reme, I'll be able to go home soon.
What bones have you brought for us?  You have the smell of the grave on you.
The Slouchbears.nnAlways more.nnAlways they return... feeding.nnA Mother becomes upset.
I'll have to remember to thank <<1>> next time I see him.nnHe's always sending me the most intriguing things.
The joy of Lurmpi's company! To be having an audience for my pearls of wisdom!
So many of our sisters have fallen, yet I have faith in <<1>> and her leadership. The last Keeper of the Tree will lead us back to harmony with nature.
I can make it. I know I can!
That one has the samples, yes?
You can find rubble to repair the barricades around the old tower to the northwest.
Ordinator Faydile Slythin is north of here. nnHe's on the docks, keeping a close eye on the ship inspections.
Nix-hounds are lurking around the guar herds. Most of the time they lair in the rocks. nnWhen they get hungry, they run down to kill our beasts.
Take whatever is salvageable from the homes of our masters and bring them to me. It is only fitting we profit from their suffering, after they profited from ours.
Did you find it? Was it all there? nnTo think of all those valuables were wasted, trapped with his useless rotting body.nnJust the thought of it angers me.
How could I have raised such a worthless son?nnMy daughter, Llira, is much more deserving. nnShe's selfless, as her mother was, and she's devoted herself to the Tribunal Temple.
Will the <<1>> be fetching the cage key?nnEntering the large tent to the south. Recovering the key.nnFreeing Elder Brump!
Hello again, friend. I'm afraid I can't do any business with you at this time, but look for me when I get into Kragenmoor!
I'm on my break. Don't bother me.
You must recover the sword Werereaver, or the entire kingdom may pay the price.

Most of my family's fortune went to this sanatorium, for Savila's care. I can return to Mournhold and declare myself cured. nnI pray that you keep this secret to yourself, <<1>>, and the knowledge of what you've done.
I know Ferema is innocent, but our... relationship may cast doubts on my testimony.
Get a drop of the purple potion, a pinch of reagent and then combine them with the bergamont seeds in the alchemy set.
One day, we'll get Camlorn back.
One day, we'll get Camlorn back.
One day, we'll get Camlorn back.
One day, we'll get Camlorn back.
One day, we'll get Camlorn back.
Is that the body of a nixad? What happened to the poor creature?
Welcome to Barkbite. Orcs think bathing is optional, so don't stand upwind.
Urgh. You can - hic! - go on through to the Ayleid Milestone.

My poor Fura. nnI can't allow myself to be consumed by grief. My child still lives, but I'll still mourn her absence.nnPerhaps I can visit her in Branglebracken before her spirit takes flight. My child may yet know her mother....
You'll find the cave behind this buildings.nnRemember, you don't need to kill the rabble helping him. Slaying <<1>> will be enough to stop the flow of skooma into Kragenmoor.nnEnd this.
My clothes are inside Catian's quarters. And could you find me a bucket of water to wash up with?nnI'm sorry. I just - I can't leave like this. People can't see me like this.
There is nothing as fine as the aroma of spoiled milk.
I'll be instructing the guards to take all the necessary precautions with our captive. nnWe'll have to quarantine him before we can prove he isn't infected.nnEbonheart will need to hear about this.
I think I'm dying! nnThat mazte was the worst thing I've ever tasted in my entire life.
No telling if any of these larvae are male or female at this stage in their development. A few more years and they'll start showing the differences. They'll make some fine chitin pieces one day!
Thank you so much for your help, <<1>>.nnWith the information you brought us, we'll be able to cure the tarn shortly.
None of us believed we might be able to regain the mine.  Yet with your efforts, we may be able to get back to work in no time at all.
You've saved my life, friend, returning the treasure like you did. I'll never forget it! As soon as I can sneak off without the undead finding me, I'm going home.
I see in your eyes the glint of a predator. Your hunt has been successful?
All this time, my brother and I have been searching for a way to gain entry to the Mage's Guild! nnThis may very well be the breakthrough we wanted.nnPlease, get me those results as soon as you can!
If you've nothing to give me, best head back down to the forest floor. There's plenty to be done at the siege camp south of Leaftower.
Have you seen to the sick yet?
No purse. Not surprising. Why do I get the feeling I'll never see my coin again?
Once we've found <<1>>, we need to put a stop to <<2>> and the necromancy she's unleashed on the fort.
Be careful. The enemy could march past this tower at any moment.
Have you the brains I requested?
Keeping well, my friend? nnI'll admit it. We don't know how this disease is transmuted.nnI'm afraid I can't offer any precautions, but I know I must continue my work here.
Have you found him? nnI'm so nervous.nnI'm quivering at the very thought of seeing him again!
<<1>> stopped to speak with me while you were down by the shore. nnShe was grateful you found me. She asked me to thank you.nnApparently, she's left for Othrenis to see to her sister's burial.
I heard the explosions from here! nnThose charlatans will be ruined! They'll have to leave Ebonheart without their fake wares to peddle.
The Huntress would drive us all into the arms of the madness that afflicts her.
Returned again, friend? The cliff racers are not as numerous as they once were. nnPerhaps the Tribunal finally heard my prayers, or maybe they responded to the blood sacrifices.nnWe may never know.
Take this Woodrune and use it to summon Forest Spirits next to the Lifetimber sapling to the northwest. Slay the Scamps that are attacking the sprouting Lifetimber.

I can't describe what I saw. nnA great and terrible power engulfed me. For a moment, I thought I peered into the depths of Oblivion.nnNow I cannot leave. I have given myself to service. To leave would mean... ending my life.
The only thing that keeps those guards honest is the thought of more bribes to come. nnI can't imagine how much they've stolen from slaves like me.
Have you the crown? Take it from Phrastus.
You'll find the slaughter fish swimming within the river to the east of us. Be light in your step for if the Ashlanders see you, they may question your actions.
I'm pleased you stopped the Redorans. nnIf they had planted those forged records, we might have faced censure in the Great Moot.nnNow I must thwart their next scheme. They never stop trying.
Those damned shadows are burning down the garden! Help us destroy them!
I can't be in two places at once. I need to keep an eye on the mine.nnBring me back a sample of what they're mining in there, will you?nnI'd certainly appreciate it.
Taking the Amberberries from his friend.nnPlacing them in his cask of sweet sugar and fremented juice. nnShaking the cask with great enthusiasm!
I read stories to all the children in the village here once every week.nnYou're always welcome to join us, dear. One is never too old to be a child again.

Will the <<1>> be using the Night Stone?nnWill the <<1>> be doing it in front of Shoom by the waterfall? nnWill the <<1>> be defeating two apparitions summoned by the Night Stone?nnCheering for the <<1>>! nnWatching from a safe distance.
I saw them leading our troops off the field. Look on the outskirts of the Wracked Plain to the south and the east. You should be able to find survivors there.nnThat's my hope, at least.
You have my thanks, friend. nnMy assistant and I will now leave these detestable ruins, so I may continue my studies in earnest.
And now? Are those fires out?
Slay Sapiarch Veyl. You will find her west of here.nnWhen you are done, I want you to meet me at the entrance to the ruins.nnI cannot leave this place without knowing you have also left it safely.
Thanks to you, we have fewer undead to fight.
Stay away from the ruins to the northeast. They're haunted. Ayleid ghosts, they say.
Don't judge us, outlander.
Be careful heading to Mireblossom. nnThe Peatwalkers will attack you, since you're not part of the Mireblossom tribe.
You're not welcome here, stranger.
Thank you! With your help, we'll be able to stay here much longer. We can endure anything the elements bring to us.nnAs soon as he calms down, I'm going to take all our ale and dump it in the bog.
Please open the cage and let me out.
Thanks to you, much of our herd has been restored. We're in your debt.
I'm glad you were able to escape the cave unharmed.
Once we're able to reclaim our mine, Crosswych will be prosperous again.
I'm glad someone else has arrived. Are you here to search for the townsfolk?
You've done so much for our family, <<1>>.  We'll always be grateful to you.
I'm not going back, so it's no good convincing me.  The bandits aren't so bad at all, and they're teaching me to fight!
For the first time since the Fragments of the Unclean were stolen, we can finally rest.

<<1>>'s house is just outside Crosswych to the south. His house might be surrounded by the same spectres that lurked outside Mari's home.nnWhile you help the locals, I'm going to turn myself in to the guards in the Southern Crosswych Tower.
Please, find out what's causing the Daedra to attack the manor. This estate is my life's work. I won't see it torn apart by monsters!
<The spirit stares at you in silence.>
Isn't my daughter just the sweetest thing? I don't know what I'd do if I ever lost her.
I am grateful for your silence, <<1>>. I will not forget this kindness.
We know they're up to something. Now we just have to figure out what it is.nnThat's where you come in.
"Arkay's Beard" or "Eyes of Akatosh?" Hmm. Arkay sounds right, but Akatosh would be more sensible.
So he didn't turn into a chicken? Too bad.
I'm glad that black cat is gone, but I'm worried about the harm it may bring to the Niverns. They shouldn't keep it around.
Have you had any luck, friend?
Don't be shy. Go light those fires!nnThis is going to be fun.

Thank you for helping. I've been so busy with my work for the garrison. I'm sure <<1>> will like whatever you pick out.nnOnce you've found a gift, take it to my love at the Thalmor. He's very important there.
I trust you adequately conveyed my intentions to <<1>>? My patience with her foolery has long run dry.

This final task will test all you know. nnYou'll need to use everything you have to win this one. You'll need to defeat both guardians at the same time to prove your worth.nnSpeak to me when you are ready.
What a strange feeling! nnHow... how did I come to be here?
It was a boon from Baan Dar that you happened along. nnWas it Janne who asked you to help Dro-Dara and the others?
Now there's a sight for some sore old eyes. I missed this stuff.nnYou've done me a great favor by getting it back.
I am safe here. The bandits fear the crocodilesand wisely so.
Tough luck, friend. Shanari was a wily old cat.nnShe was sweet as thundergrub meat.nnCare to place a bet on the next fight?
Will I ever see my family again?nnProbably not. My parents are gone, and I don't have any siblings. Will anyone miss me when I'm gone?
Don't give away my position. This is a good vantage point for observing the ogres.
My wife, Breloth, is dead. Mara take her soul. nnShe was the only good thing I ever knew in this world, and now I can't even give her a decent burial.
Ithguleoir is dead? I can hardly believe it! nnHenri can finally start fishing again. He certainly can't use Ithguleoir as an excuse anymore!
There's something really important going on in the northern huts.nnLook there first. That's where I was lurking when they drove me away.nnWhatever's in there, they don't want anyone to see it.
Steel and stone! Welcome to the Scarp! nnWe could use your help on the battlefield. Would you join us in the fight for glory?
You don't have to come all this way to give me updates, <<1>>. Just go back to that cave and get the job done!
May Arkay bless you, <<1>>.

You shattered the gems? I wish I could say I've been as successful. The temple entrance is sealed by magic.nnWe must find a way in here. There's something in there. Something is calling me. You must think I'm crazy!
I'm glad you're here. nnIf you're headed into the ruins, would you mind helping me with a small task?
This one will be busy salvaging all that research.nnWeerhat is grateful for your help.
It's just those three support beams. Be prepared to run though. That place will come down fast.nnI'll be here, hoping the ogres don't see me.
Look at Glasha's fur. It's all matted and bloody! I'll have to clean her up!nnWe can't be seen like this.
They must have known your intentions!

That assassin said that the only reason he attacked me is that I am a Nord! What a strange reason!nnDo you think he murdered all those people?nnWhich reminds me, there are more bodies for me to collect.
A zombie army!
What are you doing back here? The Codex still sits in the depths of Canulus Refuge. You must recover it, if we are ever to free Lord Cipher.
I'm gonna speak slowly for you this time.nnThe ship behind me. Break the <<1>> in the ship's hold. That's inside the boat, at the very bottom.
We shall have to call you <<1>> the Snake Summoner now!
The corprus in the eastern plateaus are always a danger.nnThey threaten everyone in the Stranded Lurk.
Did you get those reports yet?
Hail to you, <<1>>. The slayer of <<2>> is always welcome in Southpoint.
I can't believe my son has returned to me.
Thank you for finding me. You were right, and I am forever in your debt.
I'm sorry, but I cannot allow you to read from the sermons.nnOnly the diviners of the Tribunal may interpret and disseminate them.nnFor now, my intercession will have to suffice. Such is our way.
With their leader dispatched, the others will soon fall to disorganization. nnWe'll stay here and harry them for as long as we can.
If you hadn't arrived when you did, I fear I might have perished in those shackles.
I regret the loss of my brother, but his behavior put our entire House in jeopardy. There was no other way.
Friend, I have been told that the elders have escaped. nnWe have precious little time before the Vereansu realize what we're about to do.nnBe silent. Be swift.
Please tell me you've got good news.
I believe the blacksmith would be interested in your delivery.
What words have you, my friend? nnPlease. Tell me you've found her.

Even if the crates came from our town, we need to know if they're full of our weapons.nnHave the blacksmith check the make of the weapons. See if they were crafted by House Hlaalu.nnI've got a bad feeling about this.
We're ready and waiting to move up to that tower. Are you going help us or not?
I'm thankful you came along when you did. Without your assistance, chances were high that the Quarantine Serk would have been destroyed.
I was foolish to think I could keep up this charade going for very long.nnI guess I wasn't as clever as I thought I was.
I'm quite sure I did not invite you to stay. nnI'm sure you can see yourself out.
You have returned, my friend! nnWhat can House Hlaalu do for you?
Praising the superior scavenger hunter.!nnWill <<1>> be giving Hoom the treasures?nnOffering to give <<1>> the prize. nnDesiring only victory over Wud!
The displeasure caused by Hoom's victory. Wud will be sulking under his lean-to.
Welcome to Shinji's Scarp. nnOnce a quiet little village at the foot of the mountainsnow the front line in the battle with the Ironhand Ogres.
You have no reason to help me, but I must still ask.nnPlease. Take up my sword.
By aligning these crystals correctly, we should be able to channel a burst of magic through a main conduit.nnThen we can send power to each of the crystals and repower the Obelus!
Somehow I sense that getting rid of the sword will bring us rest. nnI pray that it is so.
I hope you bring good news. One of the Vereansu came by and noticed I wasn't bound quite as tightly as I used to be. Luckily, I was able to get my hands on his weapon and use it before he could.
Now that the sick have been freed. We need to attend to the pass itself.
There's still some stray Ogrim, but nothing like what we saw before.nnThose mines are infested with evil. nnMay the Tribunal bless any fool brave enough to scout out what's going on there.
Vile elf! Away with you, back to the darkness where you were spawned. You have no business here... unless, of course, you seek a slow, unhappy death. In that, I will be happy to oblige you.

This final task will test all you know. You need to defeat both guardians at the same time to prove your worth.nnEnter the portal before you. I'll meet you on the other side. Speak to me there to begin the last trial.
Are you ready to face your final challenge?
Now that my father and sister are at peace, perhaps we can all finally move on.nnAetherius awaits.

I'd do anything for Leah! I'd slay a Daedric prince barehanded for her.nnI'd climb a mountain to gather the rarest flowers!nnI'd run through the streets naked, screaming her name and proclaiming my love for her!nnShe must know: I'd do anything!
I'm sorry! You were asleep for too long. I feared you were as lost within the dream as I was.nnTell me, what did you see in my dream? What could you see that I couldn't?

I knew when I first met you that you would be the one. Well, perhaps not right away. I've been wrong before mind you, but I was fairly confident.nnLet's finish this. It would be a pity to perish before the conclusion of all of this, wouldn't it?
Give Dirdren my report and leave me in peace.

Now that's incredible! Azura sent you, didn't she?nnHere I am, down on my knees, begging Azura for help, and you walk up. If that's not divine intervention, I don't know what is.nnYou are going to help me, right?
<You've found a lifeless body.>
Barging in and killing everyone won't get the information we need.nnWe'll have to be more subtle in our approach. Killing everything isn't working.
<<1>> is so kind and merciful.
You there! Yes, I'm speaking to you.nnI haven't seen you around here before. You must be one of Tormal's newer recruits.nnI have a task that requires the utmost urgency.
Dalomer is somewhere in these caves. Do whatever it takes to get his shard, <<1>>!nnIf these fools finish their ritual, the Obelus will never be restored.nnThen we'll all be dead... or worse!
Have you talked to that useless husband of mine yet?
What can I do<(LOCAL_PLAYER_NAME)>>?
Thank you again for freeing my husband. nnDreughside's already returning to normal.
I haven't a care in the world, and there are all these handsome lads about. nnThis is quite a pleasant way to spend the day.
The well's cleaned out, <<1>>. nnHow are the paddies?
Others like to see my inventions. That's good.
You've been gone for a while. nnHave you seen Shaleen?
Ah, you've returned! Ravenna and I are getting along quite well. nnI'm not sure if his name is Ravenna, but I've taken to calling him that in our debates.nnHe amuses me.
Don't think I've forgotten, my friend! nnI have your payment right here.
The dried flowers really brought out some lovely notes in the wine, but it lacks depth.nnDirt will definitely add character to the wine. Dried herbs will alter the wine's bouquet.
I hope you were able to assist Nalvor and Hrenil with their requests.
Your timely arrival in Aldsotha was more than a mere coincidence. nnYou helped defend our town, and we'll think of you as a hero for years to come.
Poor Endal. He was one of my closest friends. He didn't deserve this....
Unbelievable! I trusted Midresi too. nnI can't believe she was conspiring with House Dres... although that would explain why Patriarch Leyden stayed with her.
They burned my stall. They burned my wares! nnI'll have to start all over. I can only salvage a few workable scraps from what's left.
I hope this attack is isolated. nnIt may be a while before we can instill a level of confidence back in our people.

My premonitions were correct. You were the one destined to save our elder. For that, I am grateful.nnBe wary in the lands beyond us. Our sisters may not know of your deeds. Those who have fallen from grace will not spare you.
Strangeness surrounds us! It is the Balac you bear, but I expected something... different. Here, give it to me. I must examine the staff.
I've been told that Aldsotha is indebted to you for your bravery here.

<<1>> is organizing our warriors in case the Imperials attack - though he hopes to negotiate a peace.nnThat should be our priority but... I confess I'm unnerved by what <<2>> says is happening in the Bonebarrows.
Welcome back! Let me know if there's anything I can help you with... we'll do anything for the town's hero!
We're not finished yet. And who knows? Maybe the Dominioners over in Woodberth will get off their south-points and come break the siege.
So you've brought the snake.nnI thought you'd be dead by now, Nelin. nnWhat a pity.
I will have the Codex examined. You carry on your journey. When you reach Wayrest, seek me out.
Ah, you've returned. Did you bring the proof I requested?
I can't believe my son has returned to me.
Before we return to the abbey, Hakam and I need to figure out which crops have survived.
I am amazed at your resilience, friend. The Ghost Snake left nary a mark on you... or your soul.nnTo tell the truth, my sisters believed you wouldn't return at all.
I don't understand how this could be happening  we have no feud with the Midnight Union!nnWhy would they suddenly attack the Abbey? It doesn't make any sense.
Without you, I'd still be trapped in that dream.nnNow we must work together to stop this threat to Stormhaven.
Have you found that scroll yet? nnThe others are getting anxious. They want to return to the Mages Guild.
You saved Abbot Durak. You recovered the Dream Shard. nnThere are no words.
I hope your search for ingredients goes well.
That's all the help we need from you right now. We need to make sure we can pay everyone who comes here looking for work.nnWe should have more work for you tomorrow.
The Prophet's portal stone will get you to the ruins. From there, you must locate the Balac on your own.nnGo with caution, <<1>>. Gods only know what else you'll find in there.
Goblins must die. All of them.
Sibelle sent you?
Please. I need your help.
I hope the Three recognize what you've done to help us.nnI'm sure they'll be watching over you.
Now we can actually put our heads to work. nnFinally! We can get to the real reason we came here... if those two over there would stop bickering.nnI swear. Every time.
May the Eight guide your path and watch over you. Until we meet again, <<1>>.

The Jolly Squalor is to the southeast, under the main tree. Do yourself a fav-nnNo, you know what? Do me a favor and stay out of it, unless you carry a big knife and a bag of healing potions.nnFriends are good too. You know any orcs?
I don't recognize you. New blood, eh?
How fares the task?nnIf my father resists, you may press the issue. Pain is a wonderful motivator, and really, I've been very patient.
Be careful. If you play the harps out of order, it will set off a trap. You may want to see if talking to Destane might yield any clues.
A new face? Welcome. Isn't this the most wonderful party? Count Hosni really has out done himself this time for Lady Adima.
I heard Barnabe react to the news. This should be good.
Alas that this could not have been an honest diplomatic meeting. However, I have no regret in quashing their insincere dealings. You were a vital part of the proceedings. Well done.
Please, I encourage you to speak to my people. Hear their stories. nnTheir tales may give you a reason to fight that much hardernnEither way, I assure you, you'll be well-paid for your skills.

Don't be a stranger now, my friend. We need more people like you hanging about here in the castle. It makes the place more interesting. nnThough I suppose if you hung about here, you'd be pretty boring, wouldn't you? Safe travels, then.
You won't get another coin from me. Off with you now!
This one is relieved and thankful that you've found Thomin.nnHilani may return to Wayrest now, but there is one more favor to ask of you.
<<1>> is in charge. He should be in the main building inside, and he should have your payment.
I have nothing to say to you.
The other day I found a hand in here. Lucky! It still had a ring on it.
We're in your debt for your timely assistance.
I came to Elden Root when my village was destroyed by Imperials.nnMaybe I should've just stayed and fought.
I came to Elden Root when my village was destroyed by Imperials.nnMaybe I should've just stayed and fought.
Yes? What business do you have here?
This is my lucky day. nnIt has to be... it has to be....
Come on, Jazha. Come on.
One time I saw a tiger take a claw to the jugular. The blood sprayed all over the crowd. It was the best thing I ever saw in the ring.
Come on, Shanari. Come on.
This is my lucky day. It has to be. It has to be.
Poor Endal. He was one of my closest friends.nnHe didn't deserve this.
Tirdad sent you? Just in time.
Thank you! nnI knew I should've eaten before I came.
These smell delicious!
Fried boar skins are always a big hit with the crowd.
That was quite a fight! Of course, that was just a hoarvor.nnAre you ready to face an intelligent foe? nnHow about battling our Wood Orc pit fighter?
You have the focusing crystals? Great! Place them in their fixtures and we can relight the signal fire.
Get lost. I don't have any messages for you, <<1>>.nnDeath will find you soon enough.
That Imperial fellow won't leave me alone. I think he's crazy!

Talk about perfect timing. Elvira's got a damn good plan, and now that you're here, we might actually pull it off.nnFight like you did at the lighthouse and we'll have the rest of the crew free in no time.
I'm thankful you came along when you did. nnWithout your assistance, the Quarantine Serk might have been destroyed!
The old man. He looks disturbed. What's wrong?
They burned my stall! They burned my wares! I'll have to start over again. nnI can only salvage a few workable scraps from what's left.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?
Thanks for your help, <<1>>. You're truly a hero.
We're surrounded by them. They're looking in the windows, hiding in the cupboards, sleeping beneath the beds!nnThe Daedra are everywhere. Everywhere! How can we stand up to a Daedric Prince?
Each night as I fall asleep I will think of what you did and the sounds they will make as they choke to death on poisoned wine.
I've heard many strange noises and lights near the ridge north of here.nnThey usually happen during the night. I spend those nights deep in prayer.

A catastrophe in Shad Astula! Misfortune caused by the taint of foreign magic! nnThat tree-licker was hired to teach "alternative" magic. She's disrupted the spirit of the Master Wizard!nnThat Argonian destroyed our great school! And you helped her!
All around, the wolves are howling.nnDid you place the remedy correctly?
Maybe I was wrong about the Midnight Swell, but you know how sailors get. It wouldn't have been long before they were causing problems in Koeglin Village.nnThe sooner they ship out, the better.

I would not ask you to pursue the patriarch. After all, any oath to enter that temple holds the promise of death.nnNevertheless, we must stop the patriarch before he destroys all of House Dres... and the other Great Houses, as well.nnI am at a loss.

That ship's going to be burning for quite a while.nnI wonder. Will the Imperials actually try hunting mudcrabs and thunderbugs, or will they start eating their boot leather first? nnThe next few weeks should be highly entertaining.
Do you dare to face the king crocodile? nnGather your friends and petition Beastkeeper Onis. A lone warrior is doomed to fail!
What's it going to be this time?
Get away from me, scarecrow sabotager!
Go on, don't waste any time. Run to the top of Nightmare Crag.nnSummon that Daedra. Kill it before they sacrifice Rozenn and set their monsters on Stormhaven!

I must opine my displeasure. I am not overly pleased with this recent turn of events. nnI am free of my bonds, however, and relatively unharmed. My gratitude is enough to stay my sword arm... for now.nnI believe our acquaintance has come to an end.
You there! If you respect the name of the Knights of the Flame then I would ask your assistance.nnBandits are masquerading as members of our order and then robbing people blind!

Eager, you are.nnAmazing how an insect that's so small and insignificant can find a way to defeat one of the finest predators of the Tong.nnYet here you stand, insect. You stand before me with our emblem.
Thanks, <<1>>! I didn't think I'd ever escape!nnTalk to Edgar. I'm sure he'll want to give you a reward.
If only more people were aware of the Goblins' rich cultural heritage, perhaps they wouldn't be so persecuted.nnPlus, the females are kind of cute. In a way.
This one has heard rumors of the one who stole the Dream Shard. nnWould you like to hear more?
<<1>> and <<2>> know more about this accursed situation than I do. nnGo. Talk to them.
You destroyed the source. Was it on the ridge? nnForget all that. Did you find Hlena?nnPlease tell me you found her.
Our prayers have been answered!
If <<1>> ever shows his face here again, he's a dead man.
Thank you for your help. I need you to free the others.
They've tied me up! I think they're going to give me to some Daedra!
The Bretons grow bolder every day. They want us out. I know it! nnI just hope Duchess Lakana can reason with her husband.
After all the time I've spent waiting, I wonder if any of the patriarchs will even be interested.
Captain Veronika runs a tight ship, but I've never met a nicer Nord.
Captain Veronika runs a tight ship, but I've never met a nicer Nord.
Introduce yourself to the <<1>>. nnI'm sure he won't bore you too much.
You've got to help us!
Captain Veronika runs a tight ship, but I've never worked with a more gracious captain.
We'll be off soon, and just when the village is returning to normal.
Ugh. Judging by the smell on your clothes I'd guess you found some tainted eggs to destroy.
Leave me. I'm too injured to walk. At least I die knowing you took a few of those bastards out with you. You have my gratitude.
Go on, give Cerone my message. I'll pay you after you deliver it.
Did you find your prize?
Normally this pen is filled with cattle, but they were all scattered during the attack. If you're bringing them back home, I'll be glad to compensate you for your trouble.

Traitor! I can't believe I thought you would help us. It is clear that you've given over to the same greed and brutality as those Primeval Seekers. nnBut why would you dare enter my personal chambers?
We've made many significant discoveries here.

I do hope I'll get to see the ruins! I've only seen centurions in pieces. nnHow lovely it would be to run my hands over one that's still intact.nnCold polished metal... untarnished by the turn of centuries....nnMmm! Makes the blood rush, doesn't it?
Dwemeris runes cover entire walls in some of the lower levels! Entire walls!nnImagine the vast knowledge they must contain!
M'zadha wonders if the Imperials are foolish enough to try sailing that wrecked ship.
Look! When the magic disappated, that portal appeared!

My mother was taking me to Mournhold to marry some local boy. I've never met him. She says he's from a good House, though. She says I should think of the Pact and accept it.nnWhat if he's ugly? What if... he beats me?
Now that the villagers are safe, it is time to reclaim the Haven.
Always a shame to lose one so young.nnI will watch over the Treethane's home. nnI will keep my vigil until Tiradil Fairlight returns to take his father's position.
You saved many lives this day. nnMay the moons shine on you.
I don't know about everyone else but I don't think Borkul is any better of a leader than Godrun.
Deliver the bucket to the guard in the tower to the east on the cliffs.
This is just one small step towards avenging my people.nnOnce I'm through with them, no Imperial will dare set foot in our lands again!
Well now, <<1>> appears at last.nnIt's good to see you again, especially back among the living.
Now we have a broken relic. nnI hope this new plan works better than the old plan.
The Mages Guild will get you to the Canulus Refuge, have no doubt. From there you must find the Balac on your own.nnNow hurry - the Planemeld hastens even as we speak!
Now we must charge these jewels.nnOnce charged, they will power the obelisks and ward Elden Root from Imperial invaders.
The Imperials attacked us with swords and blades. nnThat wasn't enough for them, was it? No, the cowards have to poison us as well.nnThat's just ruthless.
Have you returned with what Ra'Vashi needs?
This place was once used for magical storage. That is certainly surprising.nnIf not for its current inhabitant, we could make use of it.nnA secure area could help us establish a foothold here.
Drink up! Drink up!
I am glad you made it back safely.
I smell smoke, and the dogs are acting anxious. Something's happening. Better find Farmer Gaercroft.
Lushwallow crawls with danger.nnBe wary. Don't wander west.
Greetings, friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword and all that. nnI may have some contracts available soon. Come back later.
How curious! The curative spirits usually never stop once summoned.nnI wonder what this one wants to tell us?
His breathing is becoming normal again, though his brow is still hot to the touch.nnIs he safe? Did the Wyress save him after all?
He's worse than ever. Now he doesn't even remember who I am.

If you hadn't brought that egg, I would have been cleaning up the remains of sick kwama for months.nnI... regret my angry outburst after you said you'd slain the queen. nnI know it's expensive to replace her, but your actions were correct.
Do you have some claws for me?
We have succeeded - the princess is awake! And I think she wants to speak with you.
Her Majesty must feel a great sense of relief, that she can share the duties of running Evermore in these troubled times with her new Regent.
The Minister can take care of herself, all right. That's how she made it through the ranks so quickly.nnNothing gets to her, not even the ghosts.
The dungeon's never had so many folk in it that I can remember, not counting the ghosts.
I still think I would have made the better choice, but I respect your decision, <<1>>.nnThank you for helping us in our time of need.
It is a relief, to be honest. Once this plague is over, Evermore can return to its simpler ways.nnI would never have become involved in politics, but my mother insisted.
I'll be dead soon enough myself. I can't get rid of this horrible ailment.nnThank you for your help, <<1>>. May Arkay bless you forever more.
Our king has fallen. We will avenge him!
Get to Uela as fast as you can, <<1>>.nnI need to find Freyda and make sure Evermore knows of the Reachmen's spying.
Single combat always takes place on the opposition's property. You'll find the representatives aboard the Bjoulsae Queen.
I can't believe my ears! The Reachmen are using a disease to kill these villagers. Never in all my years have I seen an atrocity such as this.
Haven't you seen enough of this ship? I know I have
I wouldn't have thought a city like Evermore would use bloodsport to solve its problems.nnMaybe they do have Nord blood in them after all.
Yet another delay from the priestess, I see. nnWell, I know she won't turn back on her word. If you fulfill her request, I'll be able to enter.nnSo it goes: a favor for a favor.
It is done. The last Spriggan is dead. It is good that we eased her passing .nnNow, though, she must be avenged. She, and all her sisters.
Single combat always takes place on the opposition's property. You'll find the representatives aboard the Bjoulsae Queen.

Seek the camps of the afflicted House Dunmer. Torch their shelters.nnYou're being tested, <<1>>. nnIf you cannot prove your worthiness to the Kagesh, you should join the other beggars outside our gates.
Oh, poor you. nnWhat happened? Did you not listen to the rules? nnDid you just get outrun by my marvelous runners? There's no shame in that!
Rahira was a pawn. nnRahira must contemplate this.
What detestable revelations!
Between you and me, I'm incredibly relieved that Emeric's here, but it took him so long, I don't know whether to kiss him or slap him.
We can retake Bangkorai Garrison, as long as we don't lose hope.
Settling this matter has been taxing on House Redoran. nnWe're spread thin enough as it is. nnFortunately, we recovered the Horator's body and gave him a proper burial.
We'll face a cruel winter without our herd.
Goodbye
We raised those guar from calves. nnI fed some of them with my own hands when their mother died.nnNow I want to walk across a field of dead scamps.

The penitents at our gates must leave. They have my sympathy, but we cannot save them. Only Boethiah can perform such miracles.nnUntil they abandon their false gods, they can never be saved.nnGive them their talismans. Then send them on their way.
Yes, <<1>>?nnWe'll have more work soon, don't worry.
The Kagesh look at you differently than they look at us. nnThey'll welcome you in their village, won't they?nnYou could help me. I'll make it worth your while.
Before we begin, you must know why these spirits threaten us, and how we can defeat them.
We've won, thanks to you, but at a great cost to both sides.

There are far too many wounded soldiers to even consider a counterattack against the cliff racers.nnOn top of that, I hesitate to order my men to attack their brothers-in-arms, even if they're deranged slavering creatures.nnWe must proceed carefully.
Do you serve Evermore and her king? nnIf you do, I need your help.
The most dangerous of Pelin Temple's spirits are dealt with, but a matter of foul necromancy remains. I fear it may be what has caused this disruption.
If the cliff racers get any worse, I think the best way to get rid of them would be burning the whole damned fort down.nnDon't repeat that. I'm sure the captain wouldn't want me saying that.
I will accompany the king's body back to Evermore. I pray your choice doesn't doom us all.
I will bind Queen Therese to her charm, and she will aid you at Bangkorai Garrison. Be well.
You are unclean. Go, or I will summon our warriors.
You have no place here.
We were rude when Methel said she was going to get a cure from the Ashlanders. nnLooking back, I realize that if I were sick with this disease, I'd go wherever the possibility of a cure might be.
You must leave our camp. Begone!
I will not receive you at my fire, outsider.

As you approach, you hear a few bumps and knocks like someone suddenly getting up from the floor. After a moment, someone inside speaks. nn"You've proven yourself trustworthy, but you still need to feed us. We're starving."
So you know our secret. I suppose it was only a matter of time. nnWe have no cure for the plague, but we do have one for werewolves.
We're dealing with a madwoman. nnWe can't wait. She'll invent some new horror to inflict on us.nnThe time to act is now!

Have you ever met Vivec? I have. He was reviewing the Ordinators, and he touched me on the shoulder.nnI think he made a joke, but I couldn't understand it, so I just laughed politely. I hope he didn't notice.

Our tribe will not disappear. nnEven if we're rendered unto dust, we will remain on this land. Boethiah has promised us this, and his words are the doom of our enemies.nnNo, this is not the end, <<1>>. Tell Ulden that, and let him marvel at it.
Once the centurions are dead, their ballistae destroyed, and their banners burned, we'll be ready to end this assault.
I'm surprised you got anything out of that n'wah. nnIf it were up to me, he'd pay for what happened to the Hortator.
I hope you're not here to harass me as well.
The wolves howl fitfully into the night. The winds blow foul through the leaves. And the trolls grow ever bolder, more menacing. All this I see, but I do not know why.
I knew Mr. Kerbol wouldn't fight back. nnHe's a good-hearted man. That's why so many of us work for him.

Investigate the wagon wreckage from the Orlishkaarn raid.nnPerhaps you can discover what they're after.nnIf you're too entrenched to report directly to me, blow this whistle, and a scout should find you.
May the Divines forgive us. Father Hurrent has accomplished the impossible. nnHe has summoned the spirit of King Eamond's mother, Queen Therese!
Enter text related to the Iliath Temple.
You're in my light. Please step aside.
This is a test of our faith. We will pray to the Three, whet our swords, and return to spill the Ashlanders' blood!
At least I was able to kill one of them.

This shrine's an abomination before the Tribunal. nnWhy should we do all the work of knocking it down?nnWe should make the prisoners do it. It's their fault anyway. That would be a fitting punishment for heresy!
I never thought I'd feel bad for an Orc, especially with them trying to eat us.nnHowever, this... this is just sad.
<You hear the king's voice in your head.>nnIt's really rather strange seeing myself this way. One always thinks of one's self as young.
<You've found Raiyeem's dead body. He's succumbed to his wounds.>

You must be <<1>>!nnIt's nice to meet you. You seem familiar. Have we met?nnI must apologize if we've met already. My memory has gone all nutwally on me lately. I'm having a hard time remembering a lot of things.
Have you spoken to my Great Father, <<1>>?

You should be able to pick out a few pieces of lumber around the burned out buildings to the north.nnThe Dres already took most of the wood back to their manor. I don't recommend raiding their woodpiles. nnI tried, and got a bruise for my trouble.
Sometimes at night, we'd feel the ground shake. nnThe Dunmer said it was normal. Where I come from, Nirn stays still!
The wind from the southwest smells like... well, I think that's what Oblivion would smell like. nnIt's a hot wind that carries the sulfurous stench of refuse and rotten eggs.
Have you ever eaten a Dunmer? This one never has.nnThey probably taste like ash and wormwood.nnThis one should ask a Bosmer! They'll eat anything.

This one came from the deserts of northern Elsweyr. nnYou know this place? It is the home of the Khajiit! nnThe north is where the noble, stoic nomads wander the sands. The south is where the soft, corrupt city-khaj live.
Do you know your letters? So few seem to in these regions.nnI'll have you know that we Cyrodiils enjoy the highest literacy rates in Tamriel.

Father fell behind on his debts to Dres merchants. One by one, he sold us into slavery. nnFirst, he sold my brothers. They were hardy and strong. Then he sold my younger sister.nnHe probably sold my mother after I was gone. I hope he's dead now.
I'm glad to see you returned safely, my friend.nnOur problems have grown during your absence.
If you want to help guard the supplies, speak to <<1>>. She's at the depot southeast of here.nnIn the meantime, I'll look into getting help for <<2>>. We can't afford another spy in our midst.
I hear you've spoken with <<1>>. What's the plan?
Josselin isn't with you.nnSo do you have good news or more bad news?
You've saved us both.nnI can't thank you enough.

Good work exposing that Imperial. I hate to think what sort of information that spy could have brought back to the enemy. If you hadn't offered to help, I shudder to think of what the Imperial's may have planned for us.
Suram will be pleased to know that <<1>> is all right, but I'm certain he'll be lecturing me later.
That food saved me from starvation, nnYou've brought me hope in the darkest of times. Thank you!
Leave us.nnMy people must grieve for the many lives lost this day.
Good luck, <<1>>, and be careful.
See? I'm still here. No food's been stolen.nnI'm keeping my word.
I feel much better.nnThanks for the rations.

Everyone criticizes me for my diligence when it comes to procedure, but I have my reasons.nnWith so much corruption, I can't allow any room for error on my part.nnOne slip could be enough to discredit me.
Finally, something will be done about those criminals! nnIt's a small victory, but I'll savor it.
I don't dare try to escape.nnI'd rather be a slave than get beaten more.nnGo on without me.
<<1>> has more patience than I do.nnIf it were up to me, I'd kill any Imperial spies I came across.
Gathering information from prisoners is an important skill, but I haven't the patience.nnIf I'm that close to my enemies, I'm usually trying to avoid them ... or kill them.
Good luck in hunting your prey, <<1>>.
That's a lot of saltrice! I think the Ashlanders will be pleased.nnTake it to the shrine across the river.nnFollow the road leading west through the ordinators' camp.
Shavari is disappointed you ignored this one's instructions.nnShavari sincerely hopes you dealt with what you released ... or others will suffer.
Disgusting. Yech!nnIt will have to do. Have you the intelligence to speak, fleshling?
A Dremora wants you to kill a sorceress? Maybe she was the one who created the portal. I guess that would work.nnHave you noticed how the light reflects from the stones here? It's so beautiful.
Those trees north of Kerbol's Village are the only place to get the bark in Bangkorai.nnWatch out for lurchers.
We don't want to fight them!
I'm glad to see you helping these soldiers come to terms with what's happened.
There can be no peace here until we have a cure for Evermore's suffering citizens.

Belaal'ss somewhere in the Dres manor.nnYou see that wall there? The one they tossed me off? It's up there.nnNo, I don't know where she is. I worked in the stable. I didn't see inside the manor. You'll have to ask a Dres.
I thought I smelled sweat and dirt. nnShouldn't you be off doing petty errands for someone?
I do hope the slaves are enjoying their little holiday. More of our guards will arrive soon enough.nnThis is the heart of the Dominion, after all! They can scarcely hope to escape, can they?
I bet those Imperials don't even know how to read!
I'm so sorry I dragged you into my personal problems. nnI'm going to get help this time.
I saw you destroying that crate - be careful of those! That's fire salt dust on you, and it's unstable.
Did you hear that? Did you hear?nnThe noises from upstairs. Sometimes she-nnGo away!
I've given you the key to Navalie's chambers upstairs.nnDo what you can to... help her.
<<1>> will help, for the good of us all.nnBut I understand her fear. We must be cautious on her watch. If anyone suspected her involvement, that would mean her end.
Together, we will return Bangkorai to its true rulers.
My savior. I trust you are well. nnHave you sustained any injures fighting Dres slavers?
I've got to catch my breath from that sprint before I head to Kragenmoor.nnSeems this disease has taken a lot out of me.
Without the proper ingredients, we can't perform our sanctification ritual properly.nnI need you to gather wormwood blossoms from beneath the trees of the Bone Fields.
The Dres use the canyons east of Omaynia to pen their slaves. nnThere's only one way in or out.nnGo in. Take the manacles we need to prove their misdeeds. Then help some of the prisoners escape.
Just step back and pay attention.nnI'm sure you'll figure out when to participate.

The Dunmer took us as slaves for a thousand years.nnThey don't think of us as people, but as grubs. They think we exist to gather their crops, dig for their metals, and wash their clothes.nnMay fleshflies eat them all.
You are travelling in interesting times, stranger. nnI pray the Three will watch over your path.
Is that blood on your hands? nnI'm not judging you.nnOkay, I am... but I'm judging you positively.

When the Akaviri invaded, I was just a boy. nnI barely recall the war. I remember vague images of water everywhere.nnThat was the only time the Tribunal visited this place. My mother took me to be blessed by Mother Almalexia!

Sometimes, I like to go to the hot springs to the southwest. The smell is unpleasant, but it does wonders for the skin!nnOf course, Daedra occasionally show up there, but nobles keep telling us the Mages Guild will take care of it.
Have you performed your devotions to the Three today? You haven't?nnThen keep your distance. I wouldn't want to be sullied by the pawing of unhallowed hands.
If you can help liberate the city, we'll all be in your debt.nnGods be with you, my friend.
Hello again <<1>>. What can I do for you?
I hope these flowers travel well.nnPerhaps a plant touched by the power of necromancy no longer requires water....nnThat would be fascinating!
Greetings friend. It's nice to see a new face. The Mages Guild has its work cut out for it in Stormhaven and every member has to do their part.nnWhen you're ready, I have a task for you.
Please hurry. I'm not sure how much longer I can keep them from drawing their weapons. nnThere must be a way to break this curse.
There are lamps along the roads in the poorer sections of town. nnGo down and fix them... and don't be surprised if the local criminals try to stop you.
Thank you for the letter.nnIt's good to hear from my sister, even if you didn't see her yourself.
We've all spent time hunting restless dead, but not like this.nnFighting spirits is one thing. Fighting the reanimated remains of close friends... that's something entirely different.
The prince is still waiting for further reinforcements. nnI had no trouble keeping him away from the miasmata.
Those appear to be Argonian thumbs!nnThat means you either came to collect the reward for Irikeel or you have some explaining to do.nnYou know what? I should just give you the reward.
The Guild thanks you for your service. Far fewer evils threaten the people of this land.
I didn't mean to get caught up in reminiscences. nnI should reward you for taking the time to find me.
Let me know if you'd like me to ensure your safety by sending you back down. nnShould you choose to walk, I wish you the best and safe travels on your future journies.

We don't see any of those skooma problems around here. nnHouse Dres likes to keep merchants away from the rougher parts of town.nnIf I were you, I'd stay up here. The Dres aren't nice, but they won't cut your throat.
What can I get you today?

For the record, we don't serve Ashlanders here. nnWhen the Dres catch someone dealing with the tribes, the lucky ones get fined. The unlucky ones well, the Dres are really big on making examples.nnWe'll take coin from anyone else, though.
You've performed a good deed today.nnWithout your help, the fallen would never have found the true path.
A "2"? Really? nnGood luck with that.
May I get you a drink, my lord? Perhaps a tune on the lute? nnI've been told my fingers are quite gifted.

The talk of men grates upon my ears. Always comparing swords. One-hand grip, two-handed grip  it's all the same to me.nnNow if you could show me a beautifully filigreed sheath, that would be a different matter entirely.
What is your decision? We must proceedone way or another.
A bittergreen salad and saltrice bread? nnWhat are you? Altmer?
That's great news!nnFind the scroll my great-grandfather mentioned. It may be the key to regaining my family's honor.
Those nobles up in the manor! I don't understand them. I just serve them.nnI'm tired of hearing them complain how useless their slaves are. nnAs for me, I wash my own clothes. Merely observing...
Have you heard any news of our House's Grandmagister? Jaelyck? nnHe's been gone for some time.
Is Krothag on our side?

The Dres are proud of how no one gets sick here. nnYou know the Thovasi Sanatorium is just up the road, right? nnI bet it's all a lie. I bet they take anyone who starts to get sick and ship them off there.

Is Mount Heimlyn smoking again? It seems to do that every day now.nnI guess we consider ourselves fortunate. The fumes always blow off to the north and east.nnI wonder. Why do we never smell them here?
You need to find that antidote.nnGet it to <<1>> and <<2>> before it's too late!
I asked my captain why we don't burn the Gutter down. nnYou know what he said? "Because it keeps all the trash in one pile."nnIsn't that great? "In one pile!"
Thank the divines! It is done.nnI feel as though a great burden has been lifted from me.
Are you a traveller? Have you heard any news of our Grandmagister, Jaelyck?nnNo one has seen him for some time. We are... concerned.
Our superiority implies a responsibility. We must attend to matters the lesser races cannot. nnClearly Saint Seryn knew this when she healed the sick and taking their ills as her own.
No, no, no. nnThat can't be good. Not at all!
I saw your signal. nnI can tell from that drum you're an ally of the resistance.nnI've got to tell you: it's good to have friendly company again.
I heard everything, and I saw Baron Sorick flee. nnIt isn't right. I'm going to make sure the baron lives to stand trial.
Most of us from House Redoran are just passing through Kragenmoor. nnThe Dres don't exactly make other noble houses welcome here.

Have you ever met an Ashlander? Is it true they don't believe in the Almsivi?nnI don't understand how they can't! The Three walk among us, performing miracles beyond any mage. nnEven if they don't have faith, why can't they believe their own eyes?
You have proven how well you can work metal. nnI look forward to polishing your technique.
My father was a good man. nnI only hope his spirit can see the work I'm doing here.nnMaybe then he can forgive me for not visiting his grave.
Have we not suffered enough for our crimes?nnYou've doomed us to be cursed forever!
Go into Danarkus. They're all counting on you. We can't leave until we set it right.
I take it Felen has renewed his faith?nnThe young often find themselves lost, questioning all things. nnUsually, it's only a matter of time before their resolve matures and solidifies their faith.
Your innocence has been proven. You may leave at any time.
The wood likes you, <<1>>, and so does Master Tree-Paws.
Come to learn the ways of outfitting?
Ready to learn more runecrafting?
You return, Outlander.nnTell me. Have you found the source of the taint? Perhaps there is still time.
I hate trolls!nnI hate you! nnGet out of my house!
Nix-hounds are all around the guar herds. Most of the time they lair in the rocks. When they get hungry, they run down to kill our beasts.
Get back to the Thane and Broadleaf. Let them know what you've done.nnOnce... I recover a little... I'll be getting out of here myself.
Blessings of the ancestors to you, Clanfriend. I will stay with the Champion and assist in putting down the last of the elementals and then we can all return home.

The farseer, praise be to her name, has left me to oversee the shrine. She is in the camp of the ordinators.nnIf only I knew what she plans to do with them. nnSome here would see their throats cut, but that would only incite the nobles further.
Welcome to Karthdar... or what's left of it. nnVonov's attack left things a little chaotic here.
I've finished looking through the spellbook. It details a series of Daedric rituals.nnOne of them is marked "For Entry into Gil-Var-Delle."
You've done it!nnI hope the workers aren't exhausted from the riots.nnThere's a lot of work to be done, now that the docks are busy again.
Such a fascinating place, this Alik'r.nnI trust you found this excursion into history more palatable than the last one?
What's that you have there?
Would it be unreasonable to ask you to stand at arm's length? nnYou're redolent with the odor of those Withered Hand ruffians. It's quite offensive!
This will take time, but the dock workers will eventually settle down... even if I have to beat them all into submission!
I know selling the johads makes the most sense for us.nnMy family did not trust my decisions, and so neither did I. But now, I see events clearly. My sister and I will find our happiness elsewhere.
What have you found?
This land is my home. nnI would do anything to protect it. nnIt's good to know there are others who would do the same.

Welcome to Sentinel, wayfarer. If you've come about the docks, rest assured, I already know. nnI regret that you visit during such times, but perhaps your arrival is fortuitous. Perhaps the gods guided you here to help us fight the Withered Hand.
Roheebah seems to be feeling better already. At least we have that to be thankful for.

Finally my father stops chasing the mirage! I advised him to listen to Ash'abah weeks ago. Better late than never.nnIf you will go speak with Marimah, I will reach out to my Ash'abah contacts as well. nnWe will find a way to stop the Withered Hand.
I hope he's alright. Garis has been under a lot of stress lately.
Before you speak, stranger, know this: for centuries, a spell has bound me. Many have tried to free me and failed. nnThis prison has no lock or bonds to break.
Thank you again, friend. You saved my life back there and with my life, you saved many.

HeyI know you! We broke into Cath Bedraud together, killed that crazy old necromancer, Angrad, er  Angolf . What was his name again?nnI guess it doesn't matter now that he's dead. Ha! Good to see you!
I wonder what its like outside the valley....
I wonder what its like outside the valley....
I wonder what its like outside the valley....

My father has said that compared to the other men that live beyond our valley, my dear Devad is like unto a Daedra.nnOh, if that is so, I have no ambition to see a goodlier man! I believe I should succumb to a swoon!
You passed out all the food? What did they say?
I am very proud. Tu'whacca says that you smote this Uwafa mightily! nnYou recovered the Ward of Ansei Radan as well! The Temple is restored, and Alik'r is safer! Tu'whacca is pleased.
Thanks for all your help!
The blood spilled here will never wash free of our nest. It will serve as a reminder to remain vigilant against those who would destroy us.
You again? Can't you do your own research?
The distrust saturates the ground like a winter's rain. But even through this mire we must persevere. For what Argonian cannot stand a bit of mud, yes?
She is dead. She was my friend, and now she is dead. Why did you choose her? Why not me?
Words fail me. Wit dies in throat. Nothing good can be said of this.
This is indeed unfortunate. Rather it were you, lying dead on the sands. <<1>>.
By the Font - you live! Incredible!nnWhat bravery, to sacrifice oneself for another.
It's true. The water has been foul for weeks.
You've helped us. Don't let it go to your head.
Now you know what I know.nnSpeak. Will you denounce me before this crowd? Or will you hold your silence, and help me protect my people?
Your sacrifice is accepted. You may travel these lands freely.
Unishi's business in Sentinel is done. Time for this one to move on, she thinks.
Master Ahtah has spoken for you. How can I help?
So you found them? The news shall make this day bearable. You've done good work for us today. I won't forget it.

Now, what am I do do with you, eh? It's dangerous here. You should seek refuge in Alten Corimont, the town to the south.nnOr better, you should find someplace far from bloodthirsty Nagas. Have you considered Skyrim? I've heard it's lovely.
Remember, when you're done, meet me at <<1>>'s home on the west side of Stormhold.
Thank you for delivering the message. The soldiers are back in training and looking better than ever.
I don't need your help. Please go away. And try not to kill anyone else.
I need to find a way to find a way to recover from this disaster before my debters get impatient. nnThe people funding this adventure are not forgiving.
By Tava's beak! You made it!
Do you have the reagents?
Go to the Oortel River, east of Ten-Maur-Wolk. The Nagas must be gathering the barrels of pitch from the banks even now.nnGather some yourself, and use it against them.
<Marimah is dead.>
Still your tongue and lower your head. The dead can hear and see as well as the living. If either does there will be no escape.nnI must find out what these dryskins want with my people.

There are many heroes buried here, to be sure, but these three are the ones Ash'abah scholars are most concerned about. nnThey were extremely powerful in life, and scholars fear they could be extremely dangerous in death.
Hopefully, it won't take too long. I've deciphered many runes since I joined the Mages Guild. I like to think of it as a specialty.
You'll see the fleshfly hive in the trees. You can easily get to them using the path just behind me.
I saw your fight with <<1>>. It was an intense battle.
Getting more members is vital if we want to survive.
Can you believe it? I actually have new armor and weapons and the means to maintain them. I don't know how we got along before you got here.
My cousin, Uurwen, was supposed to meet me here in Bloodgutter, but she never showed. That's not like her at all.nnIf she'd been at my side I might not be laying here now.
<<1>> is not the right leader for the Cult of the Fang. You have the support of the whole Cult behind you.
Thank you, thank you! My champion, my savior! By the sweet Font of Harmony, thank you!
You actually chose me? Why? Am I so much better than the others?
You chose wisely, <<1>>. Now finish your job, and get us safely out of this place.

This one is unsure how you managed to calm them down, but my thanks to you.nnAhmuzi is sure they will be back again. Hopefully the port will be open soon and we will not have to worry about such things.
I hope <<1>>'s plan works. I'm counting on you to come through with the distraction. Now, if you'll excuse me, I must prepare the soldiers.
Tu'whacca give me strength! These mine doors must not open ever again. I'll be a poor man, but at least no more souls will fall into this deathtrap!
Y'ffre bless you, <<1>>!
Whatever they are planning, they must be stopped. That much is certain.
You beat me, <<1>>.  I will follow your lead from here on out.  Do not fail us.
I owe you my life, <<1>>. Thank you for cutting me loose and seeing me safely back here.

After so many centuries, it is a wonder I can still be surprised. I could not abide the necromancer corrupting my ward, but I was powerless to stop him. nnYour actions have shattered the bladebut you made the right choice. You have my gratitude.
I will administer this at once and then rid myself of the bottles.nnThank you again, <<1>>. You have given life to my son. Anuiel bless you.

And why are you wandering about the city when I told you to return home? I should lash you, but I need someone to clean the midden today.nn...Keep your wits about you, stranger. I am here to help, but you must play the part....
Welcome to Bergama. Be advised travel to the west is treacherous due to the ongoing sandstorms.

True love! Ah, it warms my silent heart. They will be happy for the rest of their mortal lives.nnAnd do not worry. It will be a full and healthy lifetime in my nest. Such prizes like these are not to be wasted!
Well met. We'll not forget how you aided us. You're welcome back any time.
Keep your eyes open, there may be more of those beasts out there. Of course, maybe they should be the ones watching out for you. You handle yourself well.

When you find one of the beautiful ladies, give them this rose. Let them know it is I, Larland, who wishes to sing a sweet serenade into their hearts.nn... On second thought, withhold my name for now. It might be easier that way.
Blow the horn when it's clear below us and we'll jump down so you can escort us out of Gallowroot.

Greetings to you, student. What knowledge do you seek? A strategy to slay your opponents? The strength to protect your allies? The power to split a kingdom in two?nnThese things you may do, and have done already. But these are not the arts I teach.
Aww, the Mudcrab's gone cold!nnPerhaps you should try a different route in delivering these if that one's not working out for you?nnHere, take some more and try to be quick about it.
Assaulting this foe will require precision.nn<<1>> is one of our best. He should have returned by now.
If the Archeins are working with the Worm Cult, we may be in over our heads. But what would they be working towards? The matter is disturbing.
Your represent your people well, <<1>>. Not many of your kind would go so far in the defense of the Hist.
Had the choice been mine  but no, it is done. Speak to me no more.
Can you feel it? So much energy unleashed!
Though they are mad and attack you without warning, don't be angry with the Lost ones. They hatched with the soul of an Argonian but the mind of a savage beast. nnBring them mercy.
Excellent! <<1>> will be eager to speak with you.

Thank you again for retrieving my dishes. Once they've had a nice soak, and we're back on speaking terms, I hope they'll be more compliant. Please feel free to visit us anytime! You'll always be welcome here.
The sky above rains with joy, <<1>>. This hatching will sprout like a garden of Saxhleel.
I will not let my kin in Alten Corimont rejoin the One. Not today.
I am bound to protect Alten Corimont. I won't fail in that. I may die, but I won't fail.nnI don't know why, but I think you understand me.

That will help. Your chopping and mine. Just keep all the noise down. Too much squealing.nnThe Archeins set up their camp in the north area of the Mire. They must have left behind something that could show us how to seal the vents.
Even with your experience, until you have spoken to <<1>>, no master of blades will teach you.nnIt is our tradition. You will find we hold many such traditions here.
I could not let him escape, though it may mean my death. I would gladly trade for it.nnLei-Kai is gone. I freed him before I came here, to find you. I fear there is nothing left for me in this city.
<<1>> has accepted you among us. That's good enough for me.
Some lights remain, but I know better than to listen to them.nnWait. They may come after me now. I know too much.nnI need to barricade the door. Please step outside.
I hope you've had some luck out there.

As if the Imperials were not causing enough brutality here, we found our Bosmer allies butchered by wood orcs.nnThese farms are where most of the food for this area comes from. We need to take it back.
You thought as the disciple did, though it appears the old master does not appreciate her freedom.
<<1>> wants a word with you.
No one should have to linger in this world after their time has come. Thank you for giving Myrinor peace.
What do you want? Your living flesh would make excellent kindling!

You have done well here in Tears of the Dishonored. You are a hero to all the Redguard this day.nnI do not know how word has spread so quickly but I just received a very strange message concerning you from the seer Thahala in Hoonding's Watch.
It is done? I fear time is against us.
This sword came from the new armaments you brought in. My old one was pitted and rusty. It likely would not have held up in a real fight.
I'm glad the skirmishers and maulers received new equipment. I'll be standing behind them should we ever get into a real conflict.
The theft of sap is a crime we do not forgive.nnWhatever Xoqui-ven asks you to do, I would lend my sword to. Worthless as that is.
We don't need any more Pickpockets around here. If you need Guild work, you need to head to Sentinel or Daggerfall.
Now there's only Nedir to deal with. No time to waste!
Be careful, <<1>>. The forest is never safe, but it is worse now than ever before.
You did it. You actually saw this through.nnAnd I thought Jabd was crazy. Welcome to the scouts, <<1>>.
You have chosen poorly. Have you not the insight to realize the true meanings of our virtues?nnDo you really wish to save this forest? If so, prove it.nnThink wisely, and try again.
My apologies. My fellow guards have informed that you're an actual living being.
I shall transport you to the Tear's chambers.nnThere is one final trial you must pass. Let me know when you are ready.
I apologise for my outburst. It was... shameful.
You have the book! A good edition too! Hurry to Tiela, my future rests in your hands!
Casnar and I will see each other soon, thanks to you. I am sure he will craft a poem in your honor or some such.
Good, you have acquired an appropriately sturdy gift.  Get it to Tiela immediately. I will not have my chances hurt by your tardiness.
Huh! You're not what I expected for the food handoff. Interesting!
Do you have the reagents I require?
You have what you required. Bother me no more.
Sharing the evidence you discovered at Fakimal's house, I was able to convince the other bailiffs to release me from the stocks. nnTell me though, what did you learn at the Magistrate's house?
After you've returned the eggs to their nests, don't forget to tell Pale Talon we want peace.
Those pirates who live upstream keep dumping their garbage overboard when they pass by. It's very unsanitary.
Everything has gone wrong! The Arch-Mage is going to be quite disappointed in all of us, and he may even be in danger!
Every way I lie, something pokes me.

Let me know when you are ready to go. We will need to find the various points of power in the area.nnI will accompany you and aid as best I can through this projection. If something should happen, I will meet you back here.
I've had a long life. I hope I've earned a quiet end to it.

You are one of Lei-Kai's friends? Do not worry. I will keep your secret safe if you keep mine.nnThe Wharfmaster bids me allow slavers to deal their goods in our harbor. It is abhorrent, but I can do nothing. But today, I will not abide this insult.

The dead boar is wearing a decorative collar. Faded symbols adorn the fur. Its throat is slit, and a bowl beneath it is encrusted with dried blood.nnThe blood must be one of the ingredients, and the bowl may be used to collect it.
Hhraak! nnDesert swallow your bones, <<1>>.
Did you do it? Are they dead? Tell me you killed them!
The sack you carry looks full... have you found that as much as Alakad is cursed, ti is also blessed?
You've been talking to those good-for-nothing beggars, haven't you? You had a chance to do business with me... but no, instead you threw your lot in with laggarts and thieves!
Living with a harpy? nnTava bless her.
Make sure those reports get into the hands of the Archeins. As long as the Archeins and Wardens are focused on each other, they aren't paying attention to us.
I will be bringing this crown to Telenger directly! He is certain to be suitably impressed.
My heart weeps to imagine the torment our poor horses must be enduring on the baking sands, harried at all sides by vile scorpions!nnPlease, hurry before it is too late!

Leave these ruins and follow the road east. You will find the once grand city of Silvenar.nnDo what you can to save the people in these lands, <<1>>.nnThe darkness that lurks out there is more foul than any I have seen.
Twenty years ago, I could have killed everyone in this camp. Now all I can think of is how much my hip hurts.
I know a spell to reduce nausea. When I tried to cast it, I start throwing up.

Your arrival is timely indeed. I'm glad my scout was able to find you. Destane was injured fighting the ogres who were carrying off the prisoners so we took shelter here to recover.nnWe need to find medicine for him as soon as possible.
By Leki's blade, please tell me you found something in Captain Munada's home!
For some reason, ever since I became a guard I've had cravings for fried dough covered with icing sugar.
Thanks to your help and my apprentices' ambitious enthusiasm, we are now prepared to hunt this necromancer in his own lair.nnIf you are willing, I would like your help in this endeavour.

As you slay the risen guards, use the Soul Gem on them. That will charge it with necromantic energy. When the gem is fully charged, you can use it on a cultist to end his life.nnThe shade should be able to tell you about Shiri's plan and location.
I appreciate the assistance, <<1>>. Just let me know when to create the projection and we can be off.

You are not of our caste. Our leaders would say I should not listen to your counsel. Yet your perspective may give <<1>> and <<2>>... new thoughts.nnIf you can succeed where I have not, I would hold it in esteem, regardless of what our caste thinks.
I have returned from beyond the veil of death to see justice served! These sons of dogs must not rise again!
Sep has tasted your victory today, Penitent <<1>>. His eyes follow you, now and always!
Why did you fail me? I thought you were my protector!

I am somewhat at a loss unfortunately.nnThrough this entire bazaar I have traveled and not once have I seen this woman spoken of. Either she hides away from all of us, or your contact speaks false words.nnWe will need to investigate, regardless.
Fear must be respected, and in some ways, embraced. But you must not hesitate, despite your fear.nnI am ready, <<1>>.
You bear an unusual power. The waves of it crash over me.nnWhat did you find in the necromancers' cave?
So. You're back.

The swords of Yokuda were not often sheathed. Our long siege of Orsinium taught us the value of patience.nnNow you must face the forces of the Breton King Joilea treacherous asp whose lust for power led to broken alliances and countless sorrows.
Thank you for finding those eggs. I've been worrying myself sick about the consequences of our foolish actions.
Gone... my crew... they're all gone.
Listen closely.nnThis is very easy to win, you just have to pay attention. M'adric even give you something to help you out, yes?
Thanks again for keeping the Maormer busy fighting the dreugh. That will definitely slow them down in their search.nnIf you're interested, I could use a hand torching Captain Ravenil's rowboats.
Why hello there! It's a pleasure to meet you. Isn't it a wonderful day?
Get out of my sight, you midden heap! How could you help him do this?
Keep your voice down! Do you want me to get caught?
Hopefully your actions will deter future thefts. Thank you.

Below our feet lies the inner sanctum of the shrine. Within beats the Heart, veiled by the blood-fueled wards of the necromancers.nnI have no doubt the fools seek to draw power from it. You must destroy whatever focus they use.
Gone... my crew... they're all gone.
Those who wander the bazaar have been transformed.nnTheir shapes... they will lose them now that their master is gone.nnMy life will soon be gone, but you can help. There is still a way.
That creature was massive. Huge I tell you!
I hope the mayor is willing to help us.

Out of respect for you and the fact that one way or the other the Gray Sail pirates have all but been eliminated, I'll overlook any dishonesty between us.nnHarus, on the other hand, may find the sword of credit double-edged
Polon was so impressed with my work - or rather your work - that he gave me a promotion! Now he wants me to be in charge of stopping all piracy on the coast! Now what will I do
The scent is strong in this area. Something must be here.nnThis one recommends you look around.
You brought on the blessing of the Elder Hist?nnI think I'll stay inside. It looks like it's raining piss!
I can never get enough of the smell of the Elder Hist's blessing. It reminds me of berries mixed with a little bit of ash.
I hear that you are helping a confused woman with her problem. You should give up this course of action. nnSome things happen for a reason and trying to change them only brings misery.
We must get word to the Ash'abah quickly. Suturah's children may decide to seek revenge against us.

I welcome you to Bergama, wayfarer. I hope you brought your gold. Our markets have goods of the finest quality, things you can find nowhere else.nnRegardless of any rumors, I assure you the city is safe. So stay as long as you like.
I've stayed still, trying not to attract attention from these spiders.nnWe can't leave without <<1>>. She may be trapped too. I'll fight my fear to rescue her! With  your help.
Excellent work, <<1>>! This wedding is just what Bergama needs.nnLet's show the Crowns and Forebears we can live together peacefully.
Talk to <<1>> if you wish to speak of protecting the eggs.
Every week, a pirate ship sails up the Gideon. They deliver something to the Worms, then leave again.nnWe never see what it is they deliver. It goes into their cave and never comes out again.
I've heard that all Mannimarco wants is the skull of some giant. In return, he'll help us drive the Pact out of Black Marsh.nnWhy do we delay?
The Prophet asked that you be sent on to Wayrest to meet him and Titanborn.nnBut you can't go yet - there's been a theft from our Moth Chapel!
I've seen similar writing on other tablets about Loriasel. If you can complete this transcript, perhaps it will bear some clue on how to enter the sanctum of the Skull.

The three welkynd conduits must be placed in the sconces for the meridian's energy to open the door to you.nnIt is the first step to sealing the Skull of Yotunmir, away from those who would use its power for ill.
I can't believe The Thane hasn't come to ask me about all these fires, yet. Hasn't he seen the smoke?nnI might get away with this after all!
The vestments are safe. nnIs there something else you wish to discuss?
Just as Lyris foretold - you have arrived. I believe you were promised something, yes?
<The Ayleid tablet is covered in moss and prying vines, but you can make out the embossed script through the grime.>
I hope you have changed your mind. If you haven't, the Keeper may be able to help you in your search.
Rhyann's home is in the southern part of town.nnShe is old, so be kind. I fear her mind hasn't aged very well and she's prone to... accidents.

Use the wand on the chickens.nnIf they happen to have the crystals, you should be able to extract them. If they don't... well, I'm not really sure.nnAs a matter of fact, don't tell me what happens. It's better that way.
Greetings again, <<1>>. I appreciate your earlier assistance in rooting out the culprit.
Well, they took my medicines. I hope you're happy.

The scrolls have shown me the vision of your success, <<1>>. With the Staff you will regain that which was stolen. You will stand victorious over Molag Bal.nnTo the final refuge. To Bonesnap Ruins, and the Staff of Towers!
I'll take care of cleaning this up here.nnGet to Mahnor and stop him before it's too late! If the Imperials are already there, they must all die. nnOtherwise my village will be slaughtered.
