I felt a surge of magic as the book was destroyed. I take it you were successful, <<1>>?
Now that we have the jewels to ransom and puffball caps for the sleep potion, we can execute my plan.
Scout Tharslen, have you - wait, you? You're... what are you doing here? I heard the alarm and feared the worst, but never expected that we'd see you again.nnDid you find my scout while here?
Is it done? Has the totem been returned to the Goblins?
You've returned.nnHas the elixir been given?
Fortune be with you, <<1>>. We are all counting on you to complete this task.
That scroll summons Azura's Guardian? nnI wonder what the guardian will look like.
What do you wish of me, <<1>>?
Take heart. If the staff can be fixed, we'll find a way.nnFor now, we've got other problems to deal with. Molag Bal problems.
I will tell the scouts of the Falls to come and start clearing this place, now that you have released the Worm Cult's grip.
I am surprised they did not melt this gear down already. Insufferable Imperials.
Quick! Lady Miranda's in the manor house. Get the antidote to her before it's too late.
My memory is starting to return, thanks to you.
How could you do that? How could you kill him?nnJust go. Go kill that Daedra. That was his last wish.
Thank you for not leaving me with this mob. I wouldn't have lasted long.
Baron Sorick is going to regret what he did to us. nnWe'll make certain of that.
What? If you're here to find valuables, get your own garbage pile to root through.
You are not Kothringi and you are not part of the Worm Cult. Why are you here?
target: You are not Kothringi and you are not part del Culto del Verme. Why are you here?

source: If you can get rid of the undead, I'd be grateful. But there are so many, I doubt anyone could wipe them all out.nnYou have to wonder where they all come from. Maybe the bodies are washed down from Cyrodiil with the rest of the garbage.
If you can best even one of my men, I'll hand over the money.
I have prepared the eyes of the wamasu. Have you prepared for a difficult battle?
And so it ends. nnI believe I will use you as an example in a parable, to explain true courage to novices. Yes, I believe I will.
I've seen similar writing on other tablets about Loriasel. If you can complete this transcript, perhaps it will bear some clue on how to enter the sanctum of the Skull.

Rajeren still sees blood on your hands, but no longer does blood cloud your sight. This one need not point out what you have wrought, now you can see it for yourself. nnOne more obstacle lies in your way: atonement.
You know what's a good way to lose weight? Tapeworms.
You're new to Wayrest. Welcome. Even if you're just passing through, your safety's important to us.nnIf you have any troubles, you just let me know and I'll take care of it.

The coterie enclaves can be found around the edges of our village. <<1>>'s  Stone-Knappers lie to the northeast, <<2>>'s Hide-Tanners to the northwest, and <<3>>'s Reed-Weavers to the south.nnMay your words be clear water in their hearts.
I'm persuaded. The Worm Cult is a threat. Dealing with them must take priority over the competition for the golden skull.
The spirits have given me many disquieting things to consider.
I applaud your efforts on the Wayrest Strangler case. nnYou certainly deserve High King Emeric's gratitude.
You need not tell me you succeeded. I watched from here.

I do not question <<1>>'s wisdom. I do question yours. For nineteen summers, I have arbitrated disputes. If your decisions do not meet with my approval, I will reject them.nnTo learn our customs, speak with <<2>>, <<3>>, and <<4>>.
The weight of a name is measured by deeds, not words.nnWhat have you done with your name?
Watch if you wish, but don't disturb me.nnWe're grateful for your help with the totem, but that doesn't make you one of us.
It's good that you've come along, friend. The Vanne family is in dire need of aid.nnIf you could untie me, we could have a more civil conversation?
Don't worry about me, I'll be fine. Just close those conjuration boxes. nnI'll be waiting for you at Tabakah's camp.
The other guilds would starve if we stopped manking arrowheads. We deserve the golden skull more than they do.
The forest has been harmed by invaders, its life taken to fuel them. Now their lives will feed the forest.
These... Imperial spies must not be allowed to flee into the forest. We must know what they know.

Praise Akatosh! You'd be amazed how many people just walk by a fellow in dire circumstances.nnMy sister and I were visiting our aunt's farm when the whole place went to Oblivion in an oat basket! Crazy cultists and Daedra are killing everyone!
Unbeliever! You walk the path to righteousness, and it was I who showed you the way.nnMaruhk, forgive me!
Follow the path down to their camp by the dock. nnThe Supernals arrived by boatsearch there first.
Tell Andre I wanted that money. There are others willing to buy this scrap.
Is that it? Is that the sword?nnDid you get it reforged?
Thank you for helping the Sergeant get Glasha back. We'd still be trying to fight our way into the cave without your intervention.
You can learn so much about a person by simply studying their face.nnThe same is true of yourself. I can see now so many things I've refused to acknowledge about myself.
I hear you are that crazy runecrafter's novice. nnJust you keep her away from me, do you hear?

What in Oblivion just happened? Something changed. It's going to be bad, isn't it? It always is. I don't know why I bother asking.nnStill. I seem to remember you, but  this is just another trick, isn't it?

Now that you have a king's writ you should study your profession under your new master. It will be hard, no doubt about it. Stick to it and you might mean the difference between success and defeat in Cyrodil!
Go away! There's no one in here!
Thanks to you, soon this temple will regain all the magic and majesty of the trees it was built for. You are truly the Viridian Sentinel's right hand.
Excellent work on the armor operation, <<1>>. This armor is really going to make a difference once we figure out how to duplicate it.
Pardon me, but have you seen the countess? nnShe's usually bustling all over the town, but I haven't seen her in days. Perhaps someone should check on her.

It's up to you, at least for the moment. Until I recover, you're the only one who can stop these fake pirates from enslaving Koeglin Village.nnThese Daedra can't fool me! I know the truth about these so-called pirates.
Remember when I told you this was between me and <<1>>? I suggest you keep it that way, <<2>>.
I trust you've earned the duchess's confidence by now. That's good.nnHave you been able to learn why she was conspiring with her father?
The outsider returns. You look worse for the wear. What happened in there?
I hope Dame Falhut was acting alone in this. nnIf there is a wider conspiracy, I fear for what that might mean for our future.

I certainly hope I'm not asking too much of you. I am, of course, in your debt. nnI just can't ignore the fact that you might be able to set matters straight up there at the castle. nnWherever you go, I wish you safe travels.
I hope Sal gets the evidence he needs so he can set Dabienne free.nnThis is all my fault.
So Dame Dabienne isn't the only one working with the slavers?nnThis doesn't make any sense.
The captain still refuses to leave?nnAll right then, we'll do this the hard way. I'll call together the rest of the guard.
The hatch is unbarred, and you may go belowdecks. The ledger is on my desk.nnI'm uncertain how many slavers we trapped down there, but be prepared. They will not be happy to see you.

To think I shared a bed with that woman and she nearly killed me  I suppose she may have been under the infuence of that crazy cultist, Sentulus.nnThat reminds me. I hate to ask anything else of you, but I think there may still be some danger.
Pascal's home isn't usually locked. You should be able to go right in.
Still no sign of my son?nnWhat if  oh, I can't even think about it.
You are an unnaturally incredible hero among heroes. You saved my dad!nnI feel like I should be sad because of my mother, but I just can't help it. I'm so so so happy. Thanks to you.
What are you doing? Can't you see that I'm spying on the slavers?nnI think they're planning another attack on the village, but I need to know their strategy.nnGo on now. I don't want to be rescued.
I'm busy overseeing the battle.nnYou can address your concerns to one of the sergeants.
So Lucas just up and wandered off again? Boy's head is as thick as stone. If he went and got himself captured by those slavers .nnI hate to say it, but I told him so.
Whatever you do, don't hesitate. nnIf you get out there and start doubting yourself, we'll be scraping you off the bottom of a rock.
Did you save my baby? They'll eat her if you don't. nnCrack their jaws wide and gobble her down whole!
Today, anyone who kills Nords is a friend of mine. Did my father send you?
There's another lost soul that needs your help. <<1>> lives   lived  right near my tower.nnOnce we have him, we'll be ready to face the abomination.
These bootless louts have climbed into their own crypt.nnThere's no way out of this warehouse except through me, and that's not going to happen.
Is that everything? That's fantastic, but we need it up at the summit.nnFind Zeli Calhagen. She was the scout who discovered the teleporter.
My heart still desires blood. Perhaps I should wet my sword on these few Blackhearts which remain?
Everyone's saying you have to fight the old champions. Please be careful. But  win!
The guards began setting the prisoners free just a few minutes ago. nnCount Hosni baffles me. He honors his word, but never thinks twice about forcing men to fight to the death.
I may be a connoisseur of cruelty, but I stand by my word.
You are brave to come here, but bravery alone will not protect you against the artifact.nnThe stronger the soul, the faster it can be turned against us.
I salute you, <<1>>. The Ravenwatch will forever remember your name, along with that of Verandis.nnYou accomplished what we could not.
Back so soon? Had second thoughts?nnMaybe you're smarter than you look.
Oh, well done. The prisoners are being freed as we speak.
Remember: mushrooms, food out of the darkness; the heart of a mammoth for strength; sacred water for purify.nnOnce all of these are in the <<1>>, the ancients' cure will be complete.
Would you care for some refreshment before the next fight?nnAt Hammerdeath, we sate all sorts of appetites.
I see Count Hosni's taken notice of you.nnYou look like you could show us a trick or two in the arena.
We surely would have perished in that cave if not for your heroics, <<1>>. Thank you.
Well met, <<1>>. Take that staff to the Prophet, and prepare for battle! It's finally time to take the fight to our foes.
The Zero Stone will restore the staff. It was laid by the gods themselves, back before the dawn.nnIt's so simple! And yet  I fear the journey will be anything but.
Help us perform the ritual to the Herd Mother. We must free my brothers' spirits before it's too late.

Before you can reach Shiri, you'll have to unseal the vault. You must destroy <<1>> and <<2>>. Then collect blood from their undead husks.nnYou'll also find one of the Ansei Wards on the corpse of <<1>>. Perhaps you can save it from its fate.
Lerineaux's manor is a short walk from here.
Thank the Greatfathers! The fever has abated.nnYou have saved me from death  and raising a monster!
There's no time to waste. The life of our King is at stake!
That ward will buy us some time. Now we have to figure out what to do next.
I know this looks like a terrible way to earn a living, but it has its own rewards.
I'm not sure I thanked you properly for your help against those Bloodthorns. nnWhen all this werewolf trouble has ended, remind me again and I'm sure I'll think of some way to reward you.
I assumed that horn was a signal when I saw the nobles run out. Good thinking.

Look for the roots of the Wyrd around the mill.nnRemember that those creatures must give up their lives near the roots or the roots won't absorb their life essences. Any creature you kill away from a root is a life extinguished for no reason.
The Duke was infected? I was afraid of that, but I hoped I was wrong. nnI've been keeping an eye on him in case  the change came over him.

I was deeply saddened to hear of my sister's death. In Alik'r, her murderer would have been put to the sword immediately.nnI wonder, though, if the custom here is more civilized. If the man was insane, perhaps he does not deserve to die.
I just want to get out of here. That's all.
Let's go. The longer we stick around, the more time I have to change my mind.
So the Duke of Camlorn is dead. nnRestoring his city won't be easy now.
Hmm, you're here. Don't see that Gloria woman with you, though. I suppose she had other business to attend to.
My sister and the other women made it here. Everyone's a bit rattled and tired, but otherwise they don't seem hurt.

The generals of the Alessian army played a vital part in the Battle of the Glenumbra Moors. Their weapons, if still intact, would suffice, I think.nnIf you manage to get your hands on the weapons, find Sarvith. He knows what to do from there.
Try not to judge the Daggers on what you've seen so far. We're a good group and we mean well.nnNow, enough talking. Let's go hit something!
Everything's happened so quickly. Father  the johads  I can hardly take it in!
When Gelvin gets like this, it makes the rest of us extremely nervous.
Shouldn't be long now.
Well, it seems we're out of a job again.nnI'll make sure his lordship clears out, don't worry.
We're not warriors. We're just simple townsfolk. We're lucky you came along.
The balance has shifted. The shadows and darkness of Mother Murk fade away. The power of the Wyrd rises.nnThanks to you.
I hid in the manor house, but armed men came out of the basement! Then they killed people!nnI had no choice but to flee, but where am I to go?

You've avenged some wrongful deaths today, <<1>>. You have my thanks.nnTake the Daedra hearts and scorpion claws to Master <<2>> in the tower north of <<3>>. I pray our honored ancestors will have a solution.
A great peace has fallen on Westtry.nnIf only my heart could feel the same.
Who's there? Stay back. Wait. Is that you, Captain Rosalind?
It's all right, Captain. I'll rally the guards and we'll make a stand at the inn. nnSee to Leon.
I will be most relieved if this fellow turns out to be harmless. But we cannot be sure until he is stopped. Please, go carefully.
What are you doing standing around here? You think I broke the seals just for fun ? Well, it was fun, but I broke them so that you could go in.nnSo go in!

If we are too late, the implications are unthinkable  for all of Alik'r.nnI've prayed to Tu'whacca, Stendarr, and even Akatosh. Though I do not hold them sacred, I will pray to the Yokudan gods as well. Just in case.
I'd wish you luck, but I don't have any to spare.
Knock the stuffing out of those hags.
Have you been to the springs? Have you aided my father in ridding us of this Daedric scourge?
Julianos's little teapot! We did it!nnI think.
My best knight will meet you inside. We'll save Alana, don't you worry. nnGood luck, Captain.
I know you wanted to go after Faolchu, but you'll see plenty of action defending the camp.
Strange. I came out here for something, but now I can't remember what. Whatever it was, it's not worth going through those spiders!nnWhy are you looking at me like that?
Soon <<1>> will leave this dangerous Lanylantown and go somewhere nice.nnShe has heard of a place called Saakatalama. Maybe <<1>> will sell something there.
That poor spriggan spirit is finally free. It is a lurcher no more. nnThrough its blood, we have cleansed this site. Everything is ready.

Greetings, <<1>>. <<2>> told me you're a friend of the Moth Priests. I know you saved him from the cultists in <<3>> and recovered the <<4>> from them.nnYour arrival is a blessing. The people of Aldcroft are in more trouble than they know.
Have we your leave to depart?
The camp is ours again. I've never seen anyone fight like you. It was  inspirational.nnDid you reach General Mandin?

If you can restore our relics, perhaps my faith will return, and we can restore the temple.nnThere are three relics missingthey represent body, mind, and spiritthe Sword of Shabnam, Majeel's scroll, and the Lamp of the Satakalaam.
We'll wait for your signal and then make our way out. What fun!
Please excuse my husband. He gets so enthusiastic.
I hope Wizard Benele knows what she's doing.
This is it. All our work has led to this.
I'm sick of the stench of fur and blood. I want this to be over.
Alinon knows what to do with those ingredients. And he knows what to do with the blood you're going to collect.nnGo quickly, before it's too late!
Thank you for directing the women here. They will be well cared for.
Green maple. North gate. Get going.
Your arrival is a sign from Onsi.nnWe must take this opportunity to strike the invaders in my home.
Make your way to the house the Bloodthorn have been using. I'll collect some things and meet you there.
You and Tamien handle whatever's going on in the house. I'll play lookout and make sure no one sneaks up on you.
Thank you for helping us, <<1>>.nnI judged you harshly before, but you must understand: I was protecting my tribe. Let this be forgotten.
We lost more troops in that charge than I expected.nnThe courtyard is ours, but if we don't push forward we'll be overrun again.

I am so happy, I could walk on water. I hear that is how they say it in Sentinel.  Casnar and I have talked about moving there, you know. nnWhether here or there, we are going to name our first child after you.
I have to admit, when Uncle Thakh's thugs came to the door, I thought they were going to kill me.nnOne thing I knowwe will certainly be able to look back at our wedding day and laugh.
Ah, the lovely clank of armor. Well done. When we get out of here, the first drink's on me. nnNow, I have some good news and some bad news.
Not here. Place my stone near the entrance to the Wyrd Tree.
Bahir is locked up in one of the warehouses.nnI can't imagine he's too happy being kept prisoner in one of his own buildings.
You found <<1>>? That'll make my job a hell of a lot easier. He'd be living proof that the Sentinel Guard isn't to blame here.
Bloodthorn cultists made a mad dash up the road. We cut down a number of them. They clearly weren't expecting to run into us.nnI assume you had something to do with that?
Good to see you looking healthy and light on your feet, walker. Did your deliveries go smoothly?nnIldani takes your presence here as a good sign.
Find a way to get into the inn so I can make the antidote. nnMy cure may be the only way to truly save this city.
I just want to build traps and gadgets. But if the Daggers fold up, I don't know what I'll do to make a living.
The ritual site you are looking for is northeast of here, just up the trail along the beach. Place the Talisman in the revealing pool there and it should force the entity out.
The souls you need to capture are powerful.nnYou may be in for a tough fight.

You're welcome to Evermore, stranger. You look like someone who's seen your share of battle, and in a time like this, that makes you a valuable commodity.nnYou should speak with Guard Captain Hjurrun. He could use your help.
You made it. Well done.nnDid you get the crown?
The tombs must be consecrated. Until they are, the bodies in them will continue to rise.nnMay the goddess protect us from such a fate!
Have you found Ishan?nnHis poor family  I would not wish them any more pain.
What happened at <<1>> has haunted my family for far too long.nnIt's time we were freed from beneath its dark shadow.
Do you understand what happened? There was no need for <<1>> to attack us. nnAll we needed was time, and we would have left  so we cursed Padesh with neverending time.
My beautiful city. nnAh, you miserable beasts. By Stendarr, I won't tolerate this abomination.
You see what's happened to Camlorn?nnIf not for you, that would have been the fate of Aldcroft.
Suffering is all I can remember.nnI wonder how long it will be before I go mad again?
You've come to the tomb for treasure, of course. Everyone does.
It's a relief to see you again, <<1>>.nnI take it <<2>> was able to find you?

I'm out of my depth here. If it comes to blows, I can't raise my sword against Prince Adrien, but I can't stand by and watch him strike down an unarmed priest either!nnThis is starting to look like not such a miracle after all.
Now comes the true test of your strength and wisdom. Alik'r needs you, <<1>>.nnYou may use the portal behind me to reach the base of the watch.
You made the only reasonable choice. The Prince would have become an abomination.
All of my retainers are safe.nnYou were truly sent by the Divines, <<1>>.

You just missed it. The ship's captain left the ship and headed toward that alley to the south. She looked like she was in a hurry.nnWhat did you find though? Anything that reveals more about their plans?
I will not soon forget your baseless accusations.nnWhy don't you go poison someone else's cup now, hmm?
And now my schedule is suddenly empty!nnWhen it rains, it pours, I suppose.
Is it finished? <<1>> is truly dead?nnAnd you  are you all right? I've been worried about you.
Arrogant Elves! They have so much faith in that seal they put on the main door, they don't even have anyone guarding the portal!nnI'm not complaining though. Are you ready to do this?
I just keep asking myself, why in Oblivion would you help Stibbons?nnI have to believe that you were motivated by some deluded sense of pity. I feel sorry  for both of you.
Oh, it's you. I'm not looking to make any trouble.
Gerric is upstairs. He has the recipe that you need.
I can't believe all you brought me was a dusty old book.
Your deeds precede you, <<1>>.nnThe corruption of necromancy was anchored in our harbor, but you have cleansed us of that evil.asdsd
Have you crafted the ring?

I didn't know Gloria was involved in all this. She does make wading through werewolves look pretty good, though, don't you think?nnMaybe she and I can get together later. Share a bottle of wine. Find a quiet corner where we can  compare notes.
Do you have the ring?
Do you have the ring?
Truly the gods smile upon me to return you to my path. This is the second time that you have rendered your aid to me.
You  don't I know you? It's so dark in here, and I'm simply too tired to think.nnAlas, the world might be denied my brilliance!
He'll be at the standing stones by Viridian Lake. His power is strongest there.nnLook for the broken statue. It overlooks the altar where he works.
You know, an army of undead can't even be killed . We're going to be unstoppable!
The roots run deep through the wood. We hear all that transpires within it, whether for good or ill.
Ah, I was hoping you'd return before  I couldn't speak to you one last time.nnIt's good Elara's not with you. I'd hate for her to see me in such a state.
<Medya's death, much like Sir Etienne's, seems to have been quick.>
I can't wait to take these to Lady Laurent. She's going to be so pleased with me.nnI am heavily in your debt, and I won't forget it.
The Wyrd have stalled long enough. Stenwick isn't healthy, and we must do what he asked before it's too late.nnGo to him, tell him what we've done. I'm short of breath and must save my strength.
Well, now, wasn't that fun? I'd fight alongside you anytime.
How many innocent people died in those mines? The Red Rooks must pay!
When you find my soldiers, tell them to get back here as quickly as possible. nnWe need to regroup for when an opportunity to strike presents itself.
Finally, someone stood up to those bandits. The townsfolk you saved are all determined to fight the Red Rooks now. nnThe resistance grows, my friend.
The Pearl is the Way and the Guide.nnIt is the light to the Far Shores and back again, as they are placed by Tall Papa's hand.
You've talked to <<1>> in Lainlyn? Then what are you doing here? nnWe can't risk an alliance between the Withered Hand and those mercenaries.
Report! nnHave you stopped the Withered Hand from recruiting the Saltwalker Company?

Ahja died while on patrol duty. There wasn't  much for me to bury. When I lost the amulet, too, I fell into despair.nnI'll never forget what you've done for me, my friend. May Tall Papa bless you on your travels!
That takes care of the mist, but who knows for how long? Let's not waste this opportunity.nnThe time to strike at Angof has arrived.
Summoning the undead in the midst of a honor duel. Villainous scum. I knew he wouldn't keep his word.nnThe chief will  disapprove. Make sure to mention this when you speak to her.
Go! Run! Why are you talking to me?nnFate does not sit idly by, and neither should you.
Maybe I'll go back out on the road. Darien and I used to get ourselves into a lot of trouble. I've sort of missed it.
<<1>>! I didn't think I'd see you again in this lifetime.nnI had hoped to get more information out of the huntsman, but it seems my plan has failed.
I'll make sure he gets all the food and ale he wants.nnI hope he can get over his distaste for warm ale, though. We're on the edge of the desert, for Julianos' sake!
I can't stand to speak to her. Make sure she understands what's going to happen.
Did you find the medallions Clarisse was looking for?nnShe's let me know that she doesn't need my help  several times. It's so childish.
What will happen to Draven now? I don't understand any of this.
You can speak to him now. I'm not  feeling very well all of a sudden.
Don't take this the wrong way, because it's nice to see a friendly face, but what in Sheor's name are you doing down here?
You'll receive a warm welcome anytime you pass through Kerbol's Hollow again, <<1>>.
Coward. You enjoyed that, didn't you? You like hurting things?nnYou're no better than the average Imperial noble.
Sit back and enjoy the race!nnIf you picked me a winner, I'll give you a good price for it.

Greetings, friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here, especially right now. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword, and all that. nnIf you want to join the guild, you should visit the Fighters Guildhall in Daggerfall.
Looks like things are finally happening. We're going to take the town back.
What?
<The dog motions to follow.>
Did you enter you lizard? Let's watch the race. I hope it's a close one!
So <<1>> has met justice at last. It is a good day for <<2>>.
Can you believe it? One of those Imperials managed to infiltrate our camp!nnI should be manning the gates, not guarding supplies.
You'll find <<1>> in the next chamber. She has already begun raising the consecrated dead!nnWe must recover the Ansei Ward before it's too late.
Thank you, <<1>>. <<2>> has set the soldiers up in a house on the eastern side of the village.

Remember, you must get the <<1>> from <<2>> before you can enter Bonebreaker's tomb and stop Leinetha's ritual. He's encamped on the hill above the tomb, northeast of here.nnPlease hurry before that hagraven's curse dooms us all!
One cannot be a great ruler without first being an impeccable judge of character. You walked into my palace a stranger, but I trusted you immediately.nnYou have proven that my faith was well-placed.
Shh! You'll scare the beetles away.
Please. Go quickly. It would be terrible if the mine collapsed and we did not at least discover my partner's fate.

Please, I need your help. I was sent as an emissary to the Bitterkite Orcs, so I could offer them a chance to join the Covenant. nnThen they attacked me! The bloody, death-worshiping swine attacked me!
The woods will be vigilant for some time to come.nnThat is always the way when the mantle passes from one Sentinel to the next.
I can feel the grip of those accursed anchors releasing. After all this time, I am free!

Please, wayfarer. I need your help. I was hired to guard a caravan out of Bergama, a family moving to Bangkorai.nnI am ashamed to confess it, but I failed to honor the contract. I abandoned themall of themdown at the oasis.

Please, wayfarer. I need your help. I was hired to guard a caravan out of Bergama, a family moving to Bangkorai.nnI am ashamed to confess it, but I failed to honor the contract. I abandoned themall of themdown at the oasis.
We need more soldiers if we are going to take back the garrison.
Nice work, deputy! We have everything we need to satisfy statute three. nnThat means Ildani is in deep desert without any water.
Without your help, I would have been meat for the jackals.
Do you see how the Imperials fight now? They are without hope. They will soon be beaten.
Excellent work! We can examine this at our leisure once we're back in Cyrodiil.nnHmm. Do you hear something? I thought I heard something.

There you are! Lorelia was starting to worry. She said those cultists were trying to mislead you again. She worried that you would turn against us.nnI knew it was all right though. Why would you possibly oppose Lorelia?
Watch your back out there.
Maybe once I've completed my apprenticeship, I'll be able to walk that straight and narrow path my father always preached about. Maybe.
I'm sorry, my friend, but my services are by appointment only.
We need to find out what the Imperials are doing here, <<1>>.nnAfter you've gotten parts of those focus elements, meet me at the supply depot.
Fast and effective! Onsi has blessed me with a capable ally in my time of need.nnNow let's take a look at what you've found, and we'll learn if fortune continues to favor us today.
A spy in the camp? On my watch?nnUgh. Heads will roll over this. Literally, if Lady Alimah has any say in it. After my watch, I'm going to hit those ale kegs hard.
Go on. Burn the disciples' food and I'll slip by. Catch up when you can.

Who  who are you? Beware, traveler. Captain Thierry of the Lion Guard has gone mad, and he's taken half his men with him.nnThey may be dressed like the Lion Guard, but I assure you, they aren't. They're bloodfiends.
Many thanks for saving us, but my mind is now filled with revenge instead of joy.nnThe Imperials will pay for their actions.
Well, seems like the captive convinced you to help him. nnI'll be interested to see what you find out.

Can you help me, stranger? I fear for my soul. I've been bitten. I can already feel the hunger overwhelming me. nnI'm too much of a coward to take my own life, but I can't bear the thought of losing myself to this horrific disease.
Is it done? Is the envoy dead?nnThen let me out of here so I can go rescue my family!
I heard you doused the signal fires and stopped the Dominion attack. nnSounds like a fine day of work. A fine day of work, indeed!
We'll forever be in your debt.

The mayor and I will muster my bailiffs and tell everyone what happened. We'll prepare for a fight, but I don't think it will come to that.nnOnce you deal with Leonce, the militia should disband. We'll sort out the guilty after that.
Thank goodness you escorted my brother.
My fault. It was my fault, but I didn't mean it. Oh, Mother is sad now, very sad. nnI hate <<1>>. I hate him! But  I kind of want to join him. And that's bad. Very bad!
Oh, this is bad. Very bad. I just wish everyone would calm down and let me think of a way to fix this.
You there! You're not some Daedric illusion, are you? I need help!
Hallin's Stand will forever be a home to you.

I haven't seen as many harpies swarming the skies, which makes me think the threat may be over.nnI'd rather hear it from my own people, but the only ones I talk to are those who've got something to complain about.
Reminds me of my younger years.nnWe've left Seius for you. Once he's dead, this all ends.

It's not safe for either of us here, and it's a far swim to Evermore. I'm used to it, but you'll do well carving a path through what's left of the Reachmen.nnI wonder where those other ravens went, though.
I hope you're not one of those gullible people. Susceptible to angry lies and wild accusations. Leonce has let the power go to his pointed, little head. It's disgraceful!
Not that I don't trust you, but there's something else going on here.nnWe must find out what it is and retake the garrison.
Thanks for bringing me word about my father and brother. They're good hunters, almost as good as their sister.nnI worry when they're gone overlong.
My sons! You brought them back to me! Thank you. nnUnfortunately, they're still unable to leave the horses' bodies. I called upon the Herd Mother for help, but  she wants to speak to you.
The clan is in your debt.
If Corpus is able to raise all the soldiers in that crypt  well, let's just say it won't be long before we all join his army of the dead.
The mammoths are safe, and the patriarch will live on to sire the next generation!
I can't believe my eyes!
Once we have the rest armed, we will be closer to the numbers we need.
It's only a matter of time before <<1>> is ours again.
Thank you for your discretion. I'm rather concerned about what's going on in Hallin's Stand, but it's not a good idea to say so in public.nnYou see, it's my husband .
Leave me to my shame. There is nothing you can do.
Though the necropolis is filled with heroes, you will only need four in your fight against <<1>>.nnLook for them in the crypts. Do what you can to persuade them to help you.
Ah. I hoped to not see this place again so soon. Nothing for it, I suppose.nnAre you well? The trip did not faze you, I hope.
If you're looking for something to use to put the fires out, there's a water barrel right there.
Elise said you'd gone to search Skorsgaard's cave. Did you find anything?
<<1>>, if I could have a word .
If you're looking for Thomas Robic, he's down toward the beach.
Imperial spies among the men? What's next?nnI tell you, I'm really not sure I belong here.
The Covenant is falling back. They're squirming like scared kwama grubs.nnNice work. May the Tribunal requite you, as you deserve.
Troll's blood! Do you need an invitation? Speak to Tanval.
Go to the west gate and help <<1>>. Garyn can show the way.
Bring the <<1>>. I need it for what we must do.nnTrees will grow where we rest, and balance will be restored.
It's a good plan. Can't say I like ghosts anyway.
Fool that I was! I can only imagine what Giron is up to. You should find out.
Shalk are all over the town. Collect their chitin and bring it to <<1>>.
Try not to drag it out. Llarevis may be a murderer and a thief, but he is still my brother.
Until Girvas finds his daughter, there will be no trust. Look for her to the west.nnPerhaps the wind that blows is pushing us to what must be.
Whatever you're going to do, just do it.
<<1>> is not with you. You must find her.
You are not of Senie. Your scales bear stains of soot, and you smell of smoke and flame.nnWhat brings you here?
Have you found Ahknara? B'vek, I wish I could see the look on her face when she meets you in combat for the first time.
Through that door to the south, you'll find Ahknara.nnSee that she is fed to the land.
Imagine what those assassins were thinking, watching you approach. Not being able to strike until Ahknara gave the signal. nnThen the flash and they're blind! Haha.
Shalk are all over town. Collect their chitin and bring it to <<1>>.
Ah, look at the dancing flames. nnDid you get them all?
You can see me, outsider!nnI beg you, help me.
Captain? Captain Hjolm?
My nix-hounds are nervous. They smell the Orcs in the pass.
Once you've got the chitin, look for <<1>> in the temple.
This might not be the place for you. We're looking for fresh recruits here. nnYou look more like a seasoned veteran. I'd suggest you seek out the battlemaster instead.
I see the vision has left you, student.
Speak to Giron and take care of anything he asks you to do.nnI'll lock down Narsis. The Maulborn won't get near my people.
Fire engulfs the elder's house. It won't remain standing for long.
She's not with you? Muck water! She's gone off to do something brave, hasn't she?
Merely mark the door with the branch.nnYou need not be a sorcerer, for the Hist has its own magic, even when far removed from the roots.
Help <<1>> with whatever she needs to prepare the ritual.nnOur lives, and perhaps the future of our people, rely on seeing this through, no matter what the cost.
<<1>> has begun preparing for the ritual. The blood on your hands will be put to good use.
The matriarch is poisoned? She's a stern woman, and I must confess I dislike her. But she's also honorable and strong.nnPoison is no way for a Dunmer lady to die.
My wife has recovered. I cannot tell you how this pleases me.
You make it look easy. At least, what I saw when I wasn't hiding and squealing like a hatchling.nnI know I'm not brave. But did you hear his voice? Mavos has returned.
<<1>> was out searching for Bjorick when the Goblins attacked the hall.nnFind my sons, stranger. And find them alive.

Troll's blood! You've saved my life and the lives of my kind. I'll ask for your help one more time, if you'll let me.nnI crave revenge. We must make the Goblin Warlord and his spider queen pay for what they've done.
Gods! I haven't been hit like that since the war. Witch must have put a hex on the Tear. nnDid you see that? Threw me clear across the room!
Check the cocoons for signs of <<1>> or <<2>>.nnThere are more spider cocoons near the beach east of the manor house.

I can't perform the ritual without my implements. I don't even have hands to pick them up! That's annoying.nnEast and west tombs, candle and skull.  And whatever you do, don't  um, do something. You know. That thing.
I  can't hold him  much longer. Use the altar now!
Lord, Mother, and Wizard! Saalu has been poisoned?nnDo what you can. Please. That's not a death a Dunmer lady should suffer.
Welcome to the Dusklight Inn. You can stay for as long as you like. We've got plenty of room.
Get that cursed thing off the door. Then we'll see what Serien thinks of my axe.
Well met! I'm on duty, friend. Speak with <<1>> straight away.
Like eels through seagrass, we're inside. Well done! As we speak, my troops are attacking the fort's main yard.
I'm surprised that a man could see the Ghost Snake and live.
My vision was clear. Your actions will affect our future. Perhaps in ways we cannot yet see.
The constable and I are taking bets on how long before Martin annoys an officer and winds up back in the stocks.nnI really do wish him the best, but my gold's on two weeks.
Try the tombs to the west. nnI know he's here somewhere. I can feel his spirit.
Is that what I think it is? Don't draw attention to yourself.nnI'll take those and get them to the others.
Investigate the shack near the docks. That's where Rhavil went.
You have the meat and the reeds? Good.nnOur Hist is on a small island north of this hut. Spread the fertilizer you've gathered around its roots.
A totem, eh? My lovely Merarii, innovating again.nnSave who you can. I'll do what I can when they get here.
What's going on in there? Have you found my sister?
Flea-bitten, mangy Khajiit!nnThose opportunistic, vile, simpering creatures are unworthy of the lives they possess!
I'm getting out of here.nnI'll see you outside, Vivec willing.
If you haven't spoken to him yet, talk to Dethisam Berendas.nnHe's trying to find his sister, and he might have a few ideas on how to get inside the quarantine.
I knew you'd help us. I just knew it!nnI'm going to see my egg-sister very soon.
Find <<1>>. He's a blacksmith. Tell him I sent you. nnBest of luck to you, outsider.
If you ever need anything, don't hesitate to ask. If it's within my power, I'll try to help.nnI'll make sure things get cleaned up around here.
Your involvement in all this is quite  unexpected. I will be watching you, outsider.

You want us to help drive off the Daggers, you better prove the rest of the Pact can fight like a Nord.nnGet yourself a drink, grab a weaponor a poncy spell, if that's your preferenceand duel three of my soldiers.
Now go. Take this knowledge and defeat Balreth.nnKill him this time!
I hear Dark Elves are milk drinkers. Too bad. I bet a good mead would loosen your back ends enough for you to pull the sticks out of them.

I need poison sacs and goat flesh so I can complete the alchemical mixture. The sacs can be found on scorpions near the camp. Most of the tribe's goats already lie dead.nnHurry, <<1>>. The Ash'abah are depending on you now.
Hurry, do what <<1>> asked!
You're back! Is everything all right at the mine now?
I still can't believe what Edrasa did. Foolish, thoughtless woman. nnI'll send her away as soon as things settle down. I don't want anyone to learn what she did, but I need time to get over this.
You could easily rise in the ranks here, <<1>>. I can sense it.nnBut I have nothing left to teach you. You should journey to Wayrest if you want to improve your crafting skills.

The shrines are outside the citynorth, southeast, and southwest.nnVivec's shrine is across the river to the southwest of Ebonheart. Almalexia's is to the southeast. The shrine to Sotha Sil is on an island north of the Argonian quarter.
Move along. There's nothing to see here.
Good. Everyone is out. nnOh, wait. That Vanguard who was with Tanval  you should probably free her as well. She's atop a tower.
Return to the hidden chamber. nnDispel whatever remains of Tanval Indoril's ritual.
Whatever you seek here, strange one, now is not the time. nnThe reliquary has been violated. My spirit demands vengeance.
You aren't the one who tampered with the reliquary. nnI need seek no redress from you. You may go. Or do you have another purpose here?
By Ayemyou've run through a gauntlet of plague and death, yet you aren't sick. How?
Find the rest of the scouting party. I'll report what I've learned to Diiril.
The Woozle, the Woozle. I must have it! Please, hand it over now.
Youyou look like you can handle yourself. You have to help me!nnThe other guards went after the raiders, but one of those Dwarven things wounded me.
You've returned! Did you recover the <<z:1>>?
I heard <<1>> asked you to investigate the murders.nnI hope you find something.
If my instincts are right, we'll be digging up a hornet's nest when we get to <<1>>.
I saw a Khajiit run out the door. What's going on?
Tiril didn't deserve this neither of us didnnI'm sorry. There may be a way to stop that creature.

Have no fear. The offering was intended to pique the Daedric Prince's interest. It worked, perhaps better than expected.nnThe curse upon you is temporary in nature. Make sure you find the <<z:1>> before Clavicus Vile loses interest.
I will always be in your debt for freeing my son.
That tomb complex will be well defended. Take care.
You've slain three minions of the Worm Cult.nnDo you think that's all it takes?
target: You've slain three minions del Culto del Verme.nnDo you think that's all it takes?

source: This plantation will be rebuilt and repopulated with many cat-man slaves.nnAnd I will work every one of them to death in memory of my Tiril.
Why do you stand here? You should run!
I've waited for you. You've undertaken the Trial of the Heart.
Another pilgrim? So few today, beyond yourself and that Dominion soldier. Are you ready for the Trial of the Fang?
I pray the Hist amber is lost to the ages. <<1>> must not control Hissmir's lost power.
You could easily rise in the ranks here, <<1>>. I can sense it.nnBut I have nothing left to teach you. You should journey to Wayrest if you want to improve your crafting skills.
You could easily rise in the ranks here. I can sense it.nnBut I have nothing left to teach you. You should journey to Wayrest if you want to improve your crafting skills.
We begin our journey as master and novice. Are you ready?nnAnd please. Address me as Great Sage.
So, any luck? Did you find the raiders' leader?
I still have my eye on you, even if the Farseer considers you a friend of the clan.
Ra-shadda will tell the moons about you, so they will always watch over and guide you.

<<1>>! It is good to see you that you have blossomed under my tutelage.nnIt is a shame that we were unable to explore your soul together. nnBut never-mind. Go to Wayrest to seek out deep mysteries of our craft.
It's so good to see everyone free again  I mean almost everyone.
Thanks for getting me out of that cagebut you could have backed me up, you know.
Tribunal's blessings. Watch yourself here in Tal'Deic. Discipline isn't what it used to be, but that doesn't mean you can start trouble.
She's not letting me out? What, am I to wait here while you do her little errands?nnShe's probably laughing at me from her decrepit little boat wreck. Never try to negotiate with criminals.
The green maple you need is very close. Can you smell it? Let your nose fill with the scent of green and growing things. A rarity here in the ashlands.
These are troubled times. But all times have trouble of one sort or another, yes?
And what do you bring me? It better be something of worth. I don't pay layabouts for rotten fruit. nnThat's bad for my reputation, but it's worse for the layabouts. I'm sure you understand.
Something is influencing the General. We need to find out what's wrong with him.
Leave me. I prefer to spend the hours before my death alone.
Mastered novice knowlegde. Ready for apprentice test?
What can I do for you?

I'm grateful for your aid, outlander.nnThe crates and potions are scattered throughout the camps to the southeast. Collect them and bring them to my farseer inside the Tribunal Temple. Her name is Tirinaat.

A little messy, but sometimes you have to take the low road, right?nnOne of your vicecanons is waiting for you. I'll let them stay as long as you're vouching for their behavior. This is still my town, understand?
I hope you've learned something.
Don't mistake my attitude. Naldyn was a thug, but he was my brother. nnI don't care who he harassed. He didn't deserve to die.
You say you can help? Prove it.nnI won't believe you until I see some results.
Aren't the wasps just adorable?nnBe careful not to get stung. The venom is very painful. Oh, and so are the foot-long stingers.
Please hurry to Gethis. None of this makes any sense.
A bound spirit. So beautiful.
I can't remember anything, though the cloud over my mind is gone. Now my memories lie in deep pools, inaccessible to me unless they bubble to the surface.
You, there! Did Maera send you? nnI discovered this resonating thing on one of the smashed constructs. I think these resonators are how that Dres rod controlled them.
<<1>> is a boisterous, loud man. If he isn't found soon, the peace and quiet in Stormhold will betray his absence.
Spare our misguided warriors, if you can. I assure you, if you use the artifact I gave you, they'll stop and leave you in peace.nnMay the wind be in the eyes of your foes.
I'm sure this will convince the mages back in Davon's Watch to forget about that unfortunate incident.

Greetings, friend. It's nice to see another fighter around here, especially right now. Our numbers aren't what they used to be. Live by the sword, and all that. nnIf you want to join the guild, you should visit the Fighters Guildhall in Daggerfall.
Vivec bless your steps, recruit. Thanks for joining the war effort! With talented crafters in the Halls, there's no challenge we can't overcome.
We've waited far too long.nnThe people have a right to be upset, and now <<1>> has paid the price.

Now that you have a writ from the Great Moot you should study your profession under your new master. It will be hard, no doubt about it. Stick to it and you might mean the difference between success and defeat in Cyrodil!
Do you have the ring?
Go and read books in the library, or examine the relics in the Hall of History, the attendants will appear.
We'll hold the line here, ensure that the Ashlands are safe. All of Stonefalls is relying on you, my friend.
Repeat the past. Summon the guardians.nnWe must see this is done.
A sad event, but as I feared. Not all trees are strong. nnHopefully, this <<1>> has taken her last victim for a few generations, at least.
You. My wife asked me not to allow anyoneespecially youinto our sanctuary. It was heartless of you to put such fear in her.nnLeave.
<<1>> is over there by the work bench. He has a recipe for an adept ring.
Quickly, soldier. Speak with Turoni. We have little time left, and my brother grows angrier by the moment.
My orders are to summon up <<1>> for you. nnThese Daedra take the heart right out of me. I'll be in the rear, watching your back.
Honor to you, soldier. I have been given my instructions. I am to summon the beast known as <<1>>. nnI summon it, you kill it, and you gather its essence. This should be easy .
Honor to you, soldier. I'll take the bloody offerings and ready them for the ritual.nnAre you prepared for the next step?
I can't thank you enough for helping my son. Hopefully he has learned a lesson.
Oh my lovely lovely crystals
Be safe up there. If even our Lady cannot tend to the fates of this Vox, you should be wary.
Have you crafted the ring?
My orders are to help you.
I heard what happened with the chieftain. Don't blame yourself.nnWait, are you blaming yourself? You forget how to read faces when you haven't had a face in decades.
Remember, it is illegal to enter Mournhold without registering at the city center. You do not want to get fined for noncompliance, citizen.
Word of the plague in the west has reached Mournhold. We were told to watch for someone matching your description. It's good to have you in the city.
Yes, just a few others to share. <<1>> will be expecting her cut. And <<2>> and his boys will need their share.nnLuckily, there's plenty to go around!
I sense the Temple is free of the Daedric incursion. We are well pleased.nnWhile you fought for my glory, I learned more about our foes.
I heard <<1>>  tasked you with investigating the murders.nnYeah, well  good luck.
I was told <<1>> asked you to investigate the murders.nnMay you find the secrets hidden in deep waters.
We've been expecting you.
By the smell, I can tell you've gathered the ingredients she wanted. Don't linger here on my account.
Always a pleasure to speak with another knowledge-seeker. Guildmaster Vanus will be pleased!
Well met. I'm just waiting for Johraine to give me the word. Then I can get us out of here.
I have to dig. I have to bury myself to make it stop! The voice! The voice just won't shut up!
Quiet! Don't talk. I have to listen. I have to get back to the dream.
You're not real. You can't be! Get out of here. I have no time for illusions. I'm supposed to be dreaming.

We need the Stone complete to contain the Daedra, finish the goblinsyou have my thanks. I hope you fathom what you offer.nnIt seems Sir Edgard and his squad have returnedthey found one stone piece, but there are others.
<<1>> is very important to me. After all, he sewed the receipts for last year's profits inside his vest!
Good work rescuing those travelers. What those necromancers would've done to them .
Meejapa mentioned that you fought a monstrous Orc.
Kill them. Make the ash safe again. nnI must find that insect, the lieutenant. When I catch him, I'll pluck his wings and watch him dance on his back.
We're in grave peril.
Hah, I can tell we'll be drawing blades together soon enough.nnNow, what can I tell you?
Good luck. Beware their blades. Even the inexperienced members of the Vanguard are deft swordsmen.nnOnce you've found what we're looking for, get back here and report to Denu. She'll know what to do.
We survived the Covenant attack! You crippled their offense from the east and west. The few who arrived were rapidly dispatched.
Three of the merchants I worked for wore the keys on chains around their necks. They were the first to fall when the Maulborn attacked, but I don't think their bodies were searched very thoroughly.
Look what the Vanguard did. They confiscated my guar pen to hold their supplies. They scattered my poor guar and laughed. nnI'm too scared to go looking for them. What will I do now?
One moment, soldier. This takes concentration.
You found it! Take it to <<1>>. She should still be resting nearby.
You've done excellent work. Our agents are in place; all that's left is to set fire to the river.nnOnce the river is ablaze, we'll strike hard from the shadows and take back Murkwater. Are you ready?
I hope <<1>> told you the plan.
Good to see you made it. I told <<1>> about you, and she's eager to meet you.
Well done. You've made quite a name for yourself among the Shadowscales. nnSoon, our services will be required elsewhere. We may need you again in the future.
Have you found out anything about the keystone yet? Why are you out here?
Ah, nothing like a little vengeance to warm the heart.nnNow you'll want to speak to <<1>> about the rest of the plan.
To take out the supports, you need a pickaxe. nnYou'll find some tools in the monks' quarters, just to the east.
This is an amazing victory for us all, thanks to you.
Namira, I revere thee! Namira, I serve thee!
Turn back, wanderer. The oasis isn't safe. Look what that creature did to my goat!nnI tell you, the gods look down and say, "Hram, you deserve a life of annoyance and inconvenience!"

Our attack was a disaster. The other vicecanons agreed to keep our forces together. Should've known they'd peel off the moment I turned my back.nnIf they weren't keeping Stormhold from tearing itself apart, I'd let them boil in a fish kettle.

<<1>> informed us you had entered the ruins to pursue <<2>>'s imposter. Whatever you did in the ruins caused a lot of panic amongst the Dominion.nnWe chose our moment and pushed out of the cave. <<3>> was wounded in the process, but she'll survive.
<<1>> is one of our finest scouts. Seeing him alive is sunlight in the afternoon.
Hold. The name's Ragara, and this job site belongs to my band.
Great Sep, I have failed to bring you a worthy champion. What must I do?
Good thing you didn't release the Dremora. We'd both be ribbons in her hair.nnBehind her there's a door to what <<1>> called the "Vault." They have Hist sap in there, stored in giant vats.
If that harlot Tevynni steals my deal, she'll regret it.
Do you desire an exquisite torment? No? Then go, before I change my mind.
A word with you before we enter the portal.
Find a way to kill <<1>> and I'll reward you handsomely.
Excellent work with the Stonefalls dead drops. I'll let you know when any more contracts become available.
My brother arrived at the inn. Do I have you to thank for this?

I knew you would understand our gift! When one of our own blasphemed against the Night Mother's teachings, it made us impure.nnBut you are both outsider and pure. And soon you will be Shadowscale, but not Shadowscale.
My mother and brother are safe, and I have you to thank. Praise the Three they survived.
Some advice, outsider. You want to fill the bowl with <<1>>'s blood.
Sithis will decide your fate, outsider.
Enough about my problems. I'm just glad you're here.
Thanks for saving me back there. Whatever you did, <<1>> wasn't pleased, not at all.nnDid you recover the keystone?
What did <<1>> promise you in exchange for the supplies? There had to be something.
Tall Papa and I owe you one, my new friend. But I need to ask another favor. If I can.
What of <<A:1>>? Have you learned what the Dominion wants with it?
Mavos, did you speak with him?
The tree-minders will know what to do. Go, now!
Whose truth is truth, I wonder? May Sithis reveal his champion.
I don't want to spend any more time down here than is necessary. We should keep moving.
You honor Saint Veloth by your actions.
Good to see you again, friend. The goblinization matrix could have been amazing, if my brother hadn't ruined everything. nnOf course, you know that. You've already seen my genius in action!
Strange meeting you out here in the wilds. After Davon's Watch, I hadn't expected to see you again.nnIf I might say it, another  minor issue has arisen.

If you wish to help, you should wear the clothing from that chest. The Dominon will see another assistant and leave you be.nnBut you haven't spent much time around <<A:1>>, so their tigers may pick out your scent. Do what you can to avoid them.
The keepers will remember you for what you've done. The Hist will remember you.
Fewer of my fellow spirits haunt the hamlet. Did it work?
Don't delay. Find that box. nnI am not the most patient man in Stonefalls.
Outside the sanctuary of the shrine, you will find the true forms of the Shadowscales revealed to you.nnUse your newfound sight, and remove this cancer from our midst.
The Dwarves were quite creative! For such a godless race. Perhaps those stands could help us get past the doors?
Why do you pollute our swamp with your presence?
I hear there's profits in Ebonheart.
Quiet! Bakkhara hears you walking like an army of drunk Imperials.
The savior of Davon's Watch, and the Virak siege-breaker!nnThank Vivec you're here. Kragenmoor has been taken.
<<1>> is near the top of the hill.nnHe's got some kind of bodyguard with him.
Well, you saved my miners, but I still don't see the Goblin totem.nnThe gold I'll reward you with doesn't multiply the longer you take, so you should hurry on.
Welcome back to the arms of the guild, comrade.
This one greets your return, comrade.
You'll be in good hands with Merric. he's one of our best men, and an ardent soldier against the daedra.
We must stop the daedra from invading, no matter what the means.
I think  they broke my ribs.
What are you doing back here? Jurni needs those supplies at the tower in the prison's western sector.
I'm not harboring any wild beasts nearby, as I'm sure you can see.
I can hear the Night Mother's voice! If she only speaks to the leader, then .
I'll stay here and try to figure out how this thing works.
May good fortune stalk your steps, comrade.
We must report to Sees-All-Colors right away, comrade.
I don't trust her type, but Aelif's all we got right now. Be wary, and bring back my lieutenant.

The seed is planted. The dreugh are frenzied by the Dominion scent. nnSaervild must be stopped, and the relics returned. The wind tells me that they are near Mudshallow Cave, in the Dominion camp. Make haste!
Servyna knows I'm only good at fighting. Why she sent me along, I couldn't tell you.nnYou look pretty smart. Bet you can figure out what the Dominion's up to.
Don't mind me, I'm just figuring out the possible rewards for this venture.nnThe name's <<1>>, and I'm here on business.
If your Nord friends send some troops our way, I'm sure we can dig up more artifacts for them.
What's going on? Shadowscales, here? Nothey can't be!
Is that really Sithis? That's amazing  oh, wait, this is bad, isn't it?
Back so soon, comrade?
Always good working with a guildmate. May Stendarr watch your back.
Master of Apocrypha, I beseech you. Send us a weapon to wield against these invaders.nnOh, hello!
<<1>> is pleased to have you at her side.
Hi! I'm Jill!
No time now! I must help the keeper.nnGo! Save the Hist. I beg you.
Good luck at the court. I'm going to poke around a bit more, then head back to the portal.
There you are. I feared you'd been kidnapped by forces from beyond.
Whatever you plan on doing, you have my full support. Just know that.
I'll make sure no one follows you. nnI'm tired of sitting on my hands. Time for some action.
Pleasure working with you. May Almalexia guide your steps, and may Vivec guard your coin purse.
I would entrust this task to no one else, comrade. You go with the weight of the guild on your shoulders.
You should speak with the guildmaster. You're just in time for another important mission.
Use the bellows to stoke the flame just a bit. Use the valve to fire it yet more. And for a truly fearsome blaze, pour fire salts on the coals.
It will be a while before Feyne accepts my choice.
Tree-Minders know many cures, for those who seek treatment.
Aelif will see you soon. She has business to attend to. Suspicions to investigate. We shall see.
I'm sorry, but I don't have time for outsiders.nnUnless you care to join the Fighters Guild. I'm sure the steward is around here somewhere.
We bargained in good faith! All fair and square! You can't have him.
Thank you again for your time on the river. One day, I hope to soothe my scales in the mud of laughter.
Pay the toll or pay the price. Something, something  rhymes with rice. Yes. Almost got it.nnI'm not good at warning rhymes yet. Don't look at me like that!
Adept, new recruits to the Guild rarely impress me anymore  but you've already proven yourself to me. Good luck in Sheogorath's realm.
I can sense  yes. The aura around you glows with good fortune. You will be the one to help me complete my final task.
I'm so glad we've had this time together. One must usually go to a public execution for conversation of this caliber.
You! Knave tells me you choose toll of flesh. True? True?
An outsider! You walk and talk, so no good for eating. Still, an intruder. You must pay the toll.
This has gone wonderfully. "A simple overseer job," she said. "Just like the old days." Why did I ever leave Kragenmoor? nnMany thanks to you for your help.
Quickly! How did it go? Was there a strong color change? Perhaps a strong smell?
I  I don't feel so good.
I had no idea I was in Vaermina's thrall. She'll never touch my mind again, my friend.
The lute's probably back where Engling did her performance, down to the south. I'll be just on the next island over. Standing upright.
Sage Tirora answered your call, Shor bless her.
You're needed beneath the loam. The stone of Shor calls out in pain. Can you hear it?
Remember, <<1>> is in the shack to the southwest. Did you need something else?
My crystal tells me you have done my terrible deed.
I'll bet you couldn't find my bongos. In fact, I wager you mocked me by accepting my task.
There is still more to do.
I saw some Dreamers packing up and fleeing.nnHave you done the deed?
Have you killed the Twilight Boss?
I tremble in anticipation.
What do you want?
<cough> I don't have long. Is he dead?
I'm happy to see you, but please keep your voice down.
I can't stay here!

Thank you for getting me out of that mine. My husband and I are indebted to you. Once things calm down here, I'll get you that mead I promised.nnAnd it'll be good stuff from Hodmar's private stock, assuming the Goblins haven't stolen it.
If you hurry, you may be able to take <<1>> by surprise. Any advantage we can get at this point is worth it.
There's only one more trial. We'll let you know once we're finished delving through Sheogorath's madness.
And the cycle of pain continues. I hope you're proud of your part in this tragedy.
How can I assist the hero of <<1>>?
Do you have it? Did you find the keystone?
I can see Wood Elves out there, but why?nnWe have nothing here that could possibly interest them.
My brother and I came here together to join the Companions, and I'll be damned if we're not leaving here together, but he's caught in the mine. Please, look for <<1>>, you must save him.
Excuse me. The keeper expects us to maintain this area without distraction.
I can't believe you actually sided with that coward.nnGo die in a hole, Goblin-lover. The Pact doesn't need any more snowbacks like you.
Stral is all that remains. His time on the river must come to an end.
Be careful, now. No telling what these creatures are capable of.
They're everywhere! I don't know where they came from. I didn't see them until I grabbed a bucket to douse the flames, and then it attacked me. A Daedra!nnMy fortunes have never looked less pleasing.
We now pause for a brief intermission. Would you like some cheese?
Did you find them? Did you find the Eyes? Let's get this door open!
You've saved us all, but the giants are gathering on the hill. The Worm Cult must have angered them. I just hope there isn't a stampede.
Please, help our comrades make it back to the watch! The commander is out there doing the same. You can help!
They keep trophies every time they kill an invader. That drum in the treasure pile should get the chieftain's attention.
I can't believe Dad brought down that mammoth. He's like Ysgramor!
You can do it! You're the champion of Treva's Farm!
Valaste awaits you at the Guildhall in Vulkhel Guard, along the southern coast of Auridon.
I don't understand. What's happened?
Well. Glad to see someone who can get things done. Good work.
I wish we'd never come here, but <<1>> insisted we'd find a way to fit in.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
Hurry my friend.  Goblins are odious creatures and every second gives them more time to think of something terrible to do to our egg-brother.
I hear a fool speaking. I choose not to listen.
You dishonor the Pact with your actions. We cannot forget the past if we keep repeating it.
So  what did you think? What was your favorite part? nnNo, don't answer that. I can see by the look on your face how happy you are!
I need to get the wounded back to the tower. Gut the bastards and climb their corpses to the signal fire.
It's done. My students return to the Hist.
Thank the Eight! You're not a Daedra.nnYou shouldn't sneak up on folks like that!
Follow the trail I left when I made my escape. You'll know his lair by the bones, blood, and smell.nnTempt him with some game, and I bet you'll get his attention.
Orkey's Hollow is north of the village. Send everyone you find back here. Good luck.
Praise Sithis! A traveler! Please, the poison's chill is getting to me. I don't know if I'm going to make it.
I hope you have better luck at the shrine than I did. Watch yourself in there!
Thank you for your help. I never dreamed we'd leave this place alive.
It's strange, but knowing he's a peace brings a smile to my face. Ulrich was a hero to the end. We'll never forget him.
If you can stop to chat, your business must not be all that important.
Get that switch on the far wall, friend.
Place the north, south, and central runestones at the entrance to Skyshroud Crater to gain access.
Thank Kyne! You have it!
Uhh  Xarxes give me strength. I'm all right adept. I just didn't realize how tired I am.
They haven't crawled inside, have they? Do you see them anywhere? Are they looking out of my eyes?
<<<1>> wags his tail happily.>
You did all right. Not as good as me, but still good.
Grab some gear from our friend here. His kit will help you slip into the mine unnoticed.
Damn me for a fool! Why did I trust that madman?
Comrade. Bright Moons, Aelif is glad to see you again. She would trust no one else for the task before us today.
Thank Stendarr! Safely back in Tamriel. nnNow, we just have to face the council.
Greetings, Vestige. Sai is recovering well enough, though he hides a great pain in his heart. His confinement has shaken him more than he dares admit.
Alive and kicking, I see. As for me, I feel a decade younger. Can you see the healthy shimmer to my scales?nnYou no doubt have questions. Please, ask. It's the least I can do after your help.
Time's growing as short as my patience. We must take action before it's too late!
Close the portals around <<1>> before the Covenant can gain a foothold.
Without your help, we'd never have been able to save the refugees.
<<1>> is back. I raised him by hand. He's more Argonian than most Argonians I know!
The Covenant is everywhere.
Please. My scales are slick. Don't send me to Sithis.
You don't wear the lion crest. Please, help.
Everywhere I see, these cowards put us to their blades. Dry-skinned wretches.
I'll wait here for you. I don't trust the Mad God enough to enter his shrine.
Jofnir continues to aid us, even in death! I'll be right behind you, comrade.
Look who's returned to us, <<1>>! nnWell, now! How did you like my candidates? Splendid specimens, aren't they?
Good to see you again.
Look who's back!
You did it! The traitor is dead, and Molag Bal's hold on Tamriel is weakened. nnYou are wise, comrade. Wise, and strong.
Remember to keep an eye out, just in case.
Did you see them? They're plotting, scheming, prerparing  but they won't get it. They mustn't get it!
You want to see haunting? I'll show you what haunting really means! None of you will leave my forest!
What happened? I saw you say something to her, but I didn't catch it.
Remember, it's the appleblossom honey. That's what I need to make the next batch of mead.
You must stop Skorvild from carrying out his mad plan. Eating giants is just so  unappetizing!nnYou'll probably find him up in the old manor house. He's been spending a lot of time there lately.
Kazok's ugly head on a pike! I can't think of a better way to tell people that Voljar's Meadery makes mead fit for the toughest Nords.
The giant's leader usually prowls the hill overlooking the village.
I'm staying right here. Skorvild won't find me here.
Please tell me you've accomplished your mission.
Please don't kill me. He sent you to get his precious meat after I failed to return, didn't he?nnI don't want anything else to do with Skorvild or his cult. Just leave me alone.
I'm sorry. I'm dry with distraction.nnIf you want to join the Fighters Guild speak to Nil, our hall steward.
These Worm cultists disappoint me. They are weaklings. Failures.
A moment, please. No one else will listen. nnI have an idea that could help turn the tide against the Covenant.
Go on. Take a drink. It won't kill you.
I don't know what you did, but my soldiers and I are alive! Thanks.
These Worm cultists disappoint me. They are weaklings. Failures.
Did you make it through? The passage leads directly to the signal fires.
I suggest you get back to your mission, Adept.
I suggest you get back to your mission, Adept.
Let Droi rest. I'll watch over him until the Kyne's Breath does its work.
Hmm?
We must report to Sees-All-Colors right away, comrade.
I must tend to the wounded.
Comrade, I must speak with you about an urgent matter!
The Skald-King is in danger! We must warn King Jorunn. The Stormfist clan has gone to the Hall of Trials, and I fear the worst.
You're back at last. Were you successful?
What happened to you? You were doing so well. Why'd you stop running?
And what, may I ask, are you doing here? You mortals  always thinking you can go wherever you please.
And what, may I ask, are you doing here? You mortals  always thinking you can go wherever you please.
What right do you think you have to speak to me?  I have no use for you.
Good security is in the details, my friend. Keep an eye out for anything unusual.
So what have you learned?
Why you look so proud, what did you find out?
So what'd you find out?

Welcome to Windhelm! You're just in time for the celebration. nnIf you don't mind me saying so, you look pretty capable and good in a fight. Just the sort of individual that Thane Mera is looking for.
Thank Kyne! You have it!
I feel a thousand years young. Your tale captivated every one of us.nnI do hope <<1>> will tell another one soon!
I can't believe my ears. <<AC:1>> is restored! Praise the Silvenar's champion!
Please, be careful in the forest. Villagers return with tales of werewolves and Houndsmen prowling near town.
Your work here is done, Arrow. But know that you will always have a place of honor in the Skald-King's court.
Thank you for saving Spinner Indinael's spirit from the Worm Cult. If she'd remained a lich, we'd all be doomed.
You must go quickly. My hold on this world grows weaker with every passing moment.
You've saved the Spinner! Now, she can join the other spirits in eternal slumber. Thank you!
Well done. As a final step, you must scatter dirt on the fire.
Master Eveline and I will be waiting at the base of the root system.
Well. You got his attention. I can feel his energies shifting. He's angry.
Fascinating. The roots do not consume you. That may prove useful.
You brought an Imperial here? What for? I ought to crush his skull right now!
What news? Have you found my daughter?
I really enjoy these impromptu celebrations!
I need to figure out what happened here. My friends deserve answers.

You saved the lives of the hunters. You ruined their clothes, but you saved their lives.nnMy father will be upset when his slaves fail to locate new prey. He'll become curious. Then we'll catch him off-guard.
You gave the orb to my sister? nnI hope you had a good reason.
I can't believe all this happened. Because of a thief and an enchanted lute.
Thanks for coming to get me.

You follow me to my home? I should bite your feet off, and see how well you run!nnThe Hound is my consort. He has shown me the way of the wilds, and we rule over the forest, together. I need nothing from you!
With your help, I just know we're going to succeed!
Goat stew! You have to use a spoon or a fork to eat it. What kind of meal is that?
I'd love to travel to Alik'r and try their exotic spices.

We're fortunate no one has perished, but I fear my Keepers have grown desperate and cowardly. Did you hear Voranil's remark? Use Daedric power? Sacrilegious.nnWe need to get Rilis back in his prison before my Keepers do something they'll regret.
Holed up in a cave. Good to hear she's still up and kicking!
Greetings in his name. I've never been to Orsinium but I hear it's  nice. We're always pleased to have new faces join us.

Ah, the smell of fresh blood. It's intoxicating. I only wish I had been the one to drain the life from their bodies.nnBut this is not about me. This is about sending a message. And Valeric has heard it, loud and clear.
I miss my friends. I don't know if we will ever feel safe in Cragwallow again.
Things are quiet here. For now.
If the spirit of the former Green Lady is appearing to you, you should find out what she wants.
I'm afraid this is only the beginning. I burn with eagerness to eradicate our enemies.
The Ternion Monks have helped you and the Skald-King. Maybe now people will understand that we are not the monsters they thought us to be.
I'm sure we'll run into each other again. Maybe even when we have a show to perform!
Don't get yourself killed, now!
Come no closer until you've stated your business.
That was no trick. That was Sai Sahan!
It's always good to see you, brave one.
I'm sure Irnskar has other errands for you to run.
Lucky shot from one of those Sea Vipers. Looks like I'll have to postpone those dancing lessons.nnDid you find the sky-key?
King Jorunn stirs in agony before he calms and grows still. These waves repeat, even as you enter his dreams.nnHis life continues to slip away. What did you discover?
Once you rescue the Silvenar, you'll need a warrior's help to get him out of Jathsogur. All the advice I can give you won't make up for a strong sword at your side.
One more wounded warrior won't make a difference. Good advice is what you need on the road out of Jathsogur. Sacrifice me and Sariel can help you after you save the Silvenar.
I'll be along shortly. I'm not feeling  well.
Free of this accursed tomb and those thrice-damned cultists! I owe you a debt. Perhaps someday I'll repay it.

There are few who can claim to have fought against the Worm Cult and survived, let alone prevailed. nnI wonder if you might be convinced to strike another blow against them. The Skald-King could use someone like you at Honrich Tower.
We've got trouble here. The Reachmen have taken over the Northwind Mine up ahead.
Did I hear that right? The hero of Eastmarch? Well met, and good to have you with us!
Were you sent to rescue us?
The Stormfists were panicked by the raging fires. We cut through their ranks as quickly as we could, but I'm afraid we were too late.nnTell me  my sister ?

It's good to finally see you with my own eyes. Thank you for rescuing me, but our trials are not over.nnThe binding stones affected my connection to the Bosmer. I must get back everything they took from me.
Spinners don't usually write their tales down. I guess since this valley's been fought over many times, they wanted to keep their tales from fading. We're lucky these journals exist!
Help Firras find the end of his tale. Not with wind and rain, but with pain and death!
The brewery's up the hill. Follow your nose, you can't miss the smell of fermenting rotmeth.nnI'll stay here and tend to <<1>>.
Thallik is just down the hall. Hakra and I have your back.
The spirits of Ysgramor's companions will ride with you against the Worms!nnTalk to Valdur before you go. And Kyne's speed, my friend!
Help! Everything is horrible forever!
I'm glad you're the one who brings us the Handfast, after all you've done.
Over here, friend. How did you fare?
The Silvenar believes you are a friend. Frankly, I think you're a blessed hero.nnY'ffre knows we need one now.
I am so relieved that Jomund is safe. Thank you for helping.
At long last! Long live the Silvenar and the Green Lady!
A simple ceremony starts the Bosmers' most important relationship.
Be careful. Something's not right, here.
The Green Lady and the Silvenar will always be in your debt. As will the spinners of this city.
I'll meet up with the rest of the crew once my tasks are complete.
We caught this Maormer exiting the hold, likely off to warn his masters. With a bit of coaxing, he gave us the information we need.
You'll probably find Lord Vurlop in the inn. Like most Nords, he enjoys his mead. And I understand that nobles can get particularly thirsty when the King is in town.
You! What are you doing here? Let me guess. You're helping Rigurt again, aren't you?

The Prince and his hot temper! He decided to hold his own meeting while the King and the Pact ambassadors meet at the keep.nnHe managed to insult both the Dark Elves and the Argonians with his posturing and boastfulness!
This is your chance. Prove your legacy.
If you're going to wander the city, might as well start on the east side of town. The homeless there tend to complain louder than the others.
It's like a veil's been removed from my eyes. No, from all my senses!nnEver since becoming the Green Lady, I've felt the power of the Bosmer, but now I sense their spirit as well.
I can't wait to hear the bard sing. I wonder if he gives private performances?
You win, outsider. We'll return to the surface.
The King's Arrow! Well met.
Just go. I'll be fine.
Sai Sahan is back with you. I've lived up to my part of the dealI trust that the rest of you will do the same.
I need to get an idea of how much damage they've done.
What a mess. We'll be eating omelets tonight, I can tell you.
I think I figured out why cats like us so much.nnIt's because we are so beautiful. And we smell good.

Do you know what that s'wit had me fetch while you were gone? Food from the other tent! As if walking ten feet would kill him.nnI got the food, though. Added a special berry, too. His stomach will appreciate it.
Under the table, just there! Did you see that? It was a Worm Cultist!
You're giving me an odd look, stranger. I'm not sure I like it. Didn't I tell you to move on? Must I have you escorted out of my Thane's keep?
I don't trust you. Hallfrida looks disgusted. No doubt you've done something.
I overheard your conversation with the thane. Let me know immediately if her advisors find anything.
Good, good. Need to hold the line here. Can't let the Captain down, yeah?
Thank you.nnOh, and when you meet whoever's responsible for this  twist the knife a little? Just for me.
Help Imiril. Rilis has a twisted fascination with her.nnI'd wager she's alive, though I doubt she's enjoying herself.
The Three smile on me today. My silk sits again in my stores, and Turil must wallow in his misery.
You gave away my silk to that  that netch. Does it bring you joy to steal from an old Dark Elf?
Thorulf's room is on the first floor of the manor, on the eastern side. Sirkidur has a skeleton key, but I'm not sure how to get it from her.
Thanks for meeting me here. Please stay until I'm officially a sage. It means a lot to me.
