<<1>> is with you? Can I see her?
<<1>> researched this ruin for a reason. The river has brought us here.nnWe must explore until we've uncovered her purpose or died with a blade in our skulls.
You don't look infected. I guess you're all right.
Come now. Aren't you two done in there yet? Aelif is not sure why Merric is so green with envy. nnShe was more than happy to see you accompany the guildmaster into the portal.

Who knows what <<1>> thought she was after? What clawless fool records her plan in a journal?nnAelif would like to point out that the Dwarves believed in nothing. What would they know of Molag Bal's plot?
Comrade, I'm glad you're going with <<1>>. Her passion to discover Doshia's goal is all-consuming. I fear it will cloud her judgement. nnStendarr watch over you both.
Well, at least they're all accounted for. No more dares for me.
You! Thank Kyne. You want to do something about these ropes?
Thank Kyne! A familiar face. How did you know to come here, my friend?
I hope you're up to the task. Some of my best warriors have fallen attempting to push out those cultists.
I'm going to make it. I am! I'll live to see Riften and hoist a pint. Thank you, my friend.
<<1>> won't be safe until Treehenge is secure.
Do what you must to save <<1>>.
Why must the Worm Cult meddle in Bosmer affairs?
I'm getting stronger every minute. I wonder what my sprout will look like?
Continue your journey, wherever your path leads.nnWe'll contact you once we know more about these recent events.
Do not linger here. Danger threatens elsewhere.
A new face? What brings you to this godsforsaken place?
I'm sure with a little coaxing <<1>> will get the job done. He's far from the best performer on the island. But at least he's awake.
This one has business to take care of. Aelif has her suspicions.
You should speak with the guildmaster. You're just in time for another important mission.
I need to get my daggers.
I'll wait here for you. I don't trust the Mad God enough to approach his shrine.
Look who's returned to us, <<1>>! nnWell now, how did you like my candidates? Splendid specimens, aren't they?
Find the book in Sheogorath's realm.
Did you see them? They're plotting, scheming, perparing. But they won't get it. They mustn't.
I hope you can help Merric at-Aswala with whatever it is he needs.
There's only one more trial. We'll let you know once we're finished delving through Sheogorath's madness.
Go, investigate Betar-Nes's home. I don't trust these locals to do a thorough search. You, I can trust.
I hope the Worm Cult has been shattered. But I fear they are just the foot of the mountain.
Hero, huh? Good luck in the mines. The Reach are bloody-minded bastards.
Place the <<mz:1>> in the final two sconces so we can enter the shrine.
I have great news for you, Adept!
I am the Watcher at the Bridge. I guard the border between this world and Sovngarde.
Listen! This is marvelous!nnDown this ramp lies the hollow chamber in which our story can be lured from skin to flesh!
Thank the Three, you're not a Daedra. You shouldn't sneak up on folks like that!
Well, that was easy, eh? It gets harder from here.
Like a spring torrent, our troops will pour through the pass you've opened.
The braziers I've prepared will harness the power of the shards of Wuuthrad. Gather all that you can.nnWhen I give the word, activate the brazier to unleash the power of each shard.
You have to get out of here!
Welcome back, adept. We're ready to take control of the island from Sheogorath.
That was well done. I'm sure the Wood Orcs will be back, but now we have a foothold on this side of the bridge.nnWe'll need to keep fighting, if we want to hold it.
You've done it! By the gods, the lieutenant would be proud.nnWe've killed or rounded up most of the Ra Gada invaders. The militia won't have a problem with them anymore!
Remember to keep an eye out, just in case.
Good to see you again.

The mercenaries of the Gold Coast drink our wine and eat our food. They are waiting. For what, we must find out.nnI've heard of a courier's arrival within the hour. I need his message before it gets into the hands of the Gold Coast.
I'll do whatever the lieutenant says, so long as Velyn Harbor is saved.
Our worst nightmare has come to life. Sinmur has returned. The ancient enemy of the Companions must be faced once more.
Have you ever thought of becoming a brewer's assistant? We could go after even more unusual ingredients.
Ready?
I will seek out these monks once I make sure everything here is all right.nnI will see you soon.
Don't bother  with a whole tree. Just gather kindling. Plenty of branches down.
Best-case scenario? They've found the Mora. I don't want to think about the worst-case. Too many variables.
Be careful.
I've never seen the <<1>> look like this before. It's wonderful!
Are you the one the sergeant spoke of? She's very complimentary. I'm sure she'd like to talk to you again.
What the ? What just happened?
Someone finally shut that lizard up. Great work out there, and some mighty fine shooting.
The Maormer around the lighthouse should have a rune that opens the barrier on the lighthouse's front door. Shake a few of those beach lizards down. I'm sure the rune will fall out.
You made it, and in one piece too. I thought my leg was going to give out crossing the water.nnBut enough of that. Did you locate my things?
You should find the Black Dagger camp west of here. Please recover our claw!
Go carefully on the roads, my friend. You're a valuable resource to the Dominion. nnAnd me, of course.
You've returned. And with the spell-lattice?
Another blade for the fight, eh? Are there lots more behind you?
<<1>> has a keen mind and a good heart. She's the key to freeing Ezduiin.
Thank the Earth Bones you're here!
Oh good. She made it to the entrance of the tombs. Fantastic.
You need to speak with my Sister of Floods.
Good to see her on her feet. She's got a will of iron, our captain.
They're stealing  my memories!
What fascinating artifacts these stones are. I wonder where they came from?
<<1>> asked me to thank you for gathering all the shards. He brought them into the ruins for the final battle.
Thank The Eight! Quickly! Untie us!
The fighting has been difficult, my friend. It's good to see you still alive.
Are you done with your business in Wilding Run? The Silvenar needs you at the city of Silvenar, just up the road.
The Veiled Heritance is behind this madness, I'm sure of it!
Kyne speed youand if you run into any Worm Cultists, squash a few for me!
The spirits won't be appeased without a sacrifice of some kind.nnI don't believe they'll want a life for a life, but one must never be too careful.
Vadda'ra couldn't save them. Not a single soul. They all died because Vadda'ra was not skilled enough.
You're on your way to the dig site? The supplies Telenger's been screaming about, no doubt.
You're the one the Silvenar told us to expect. Good. I could use a strong arm.nnAgent Lanuume was right. The Green Hunters want to destabilize the Dominion. We need their plans to figure out how.
If you can get Yiri to come back to me  well, you'll be my hero today.
You made it! Thank you for saving the other minstrels!nnIf only we had our instruments .
You bastards! I murdered you! I cut your throats and watched you bleed out like stuck pigs!
I don't know if we're ready to play yet. We should go back to the camp and practice.
Buzul won't ruin the performance by limping. Drummers don't need to move much.
Ni-po-tu-la-hee! Ni-po-tu-la-hee!nnExcuse me, you're interrupting my practice.
What was all the muttering about? Go on, clear out. I've got work to do.
We can cast a spell powerful enough to blast the giants from their perches but someone needs to get close enough to cast it.
This isn't over yet. Remain vigilant, my friend.
Rotmeth for everyone! That is, as many of the guests as can stomach it.
Haven't the Draugr killed you yet?
Damn Redguard. Nothing but thieves if you ask me.
Come to see how I'm doing? Don't worryI'll recover. Really, I'm just happy to have cleaned up a bit.
Once you lead us to the top of <<1>>, the battle against <<2>> can begin!
We're counting on you to clear the route to the top of the mountain.
You returned! I kiss the two moons in thanks!nnThe mercenaries await. The merchants arranged a strange bargain for them.
Clear a path for the troops! We must deal with <<1>>.
I hope Urcelmo's plan is successful. Those Daedra frighten me.
Whatever you plan on doing, I hope you do it quickly. We can't hold here for long.
Now for the portals.
Now we take down the portals! Take them all down.
Welcome to Lord Sanguine's celebration, mortal. My lord requires you to perform a simple task. But have no fear, it will benefit us both.
Since your impressive feat in Vulkhel Guard, you're all the Queen can talk about.
The Pellingares are one of the most esteemed families in Wayrest. Or, they were, before today. They've a long history of lawmakers and politicians in their line.  Such a waste.
Beat a champion and you become a champion.
Hah! I won five coins betting on you. Thanks!
Good luck out there! You'll need it.
What was that line again?
What can I pour you?
Some of the guards are willing to help us, but they need an excuse. If you search Bar-Neeus's stall, you might find illegal wares. My family would be in your debt.
I assure you. I have plenty of names. I just can't say most of them in polite company.
Ah, you again. You look terrible. Something wrong?
Everything's going to be fine. We're just very worried about the poor victims in the mine.nnDoes everyone have their salve?
Truly Kyne guided your steps. An achievement to be proud of!
My friend. It is good to see you again. You are welcome anytime.
Well, what do you say? What was the answer to my first riddle?
Almost wish I could take the trials myself. It's been too many years.
The gates are closed. And Tamriel is just a little bit safer.nnWhat do you say we put an end to Estre?
What am I going to do? They've been taken!
Listen to me, please! They've all been takenAdelsar, Hara-Na, Varryn, even Captain Viveka. I can't go back there!
Gullveig would have sacrificed me as well, if not for your help.
She's encamped just outside of town. With her followers. Put them all down, for the good of the Pact.
You've too kind. I wouldn't dare go back to the Mages Guild without one of his books.nnMaybe two. With an autograph, please.
The Prophet's the one you want to talk to. I'm busy cracking skulls!
Thank you. I heard what you said andthank you.
Haven't seen you around here before. Probably want to make yourself scarce. Town's got a plague. Bad one.
If you're here to help, speak to Sinien.
Did Urcelmo send you? It's about time they found someone.
Here to help? You'll want to speak to Sinien.
Leave me be.
Finish her. Show no mercy!
You were saying something? About not being here?
Go on. Go have a drink and sing for us.
Eh. I've seen better. But good enough for now.
Sorry friend. This area's off limits.
Don't listen to what that traitor said. Tell the Canonreeve!
Battle will guide you forward, glory shall follow behind, and death shall lurk beyond the edge of your sight. Go carefully.
What? What just happened?
Dirty work out there. Glad we have you on our side.
Did you strike a bargain with Deros and his crew? Did they rise to the bait?
Causing trouble, you dingy dung herder? Don't think you can scare me off so easily.nnI won't leave till that Redguard hands over what's due.
I've done all I can with Jorald's wound. I think he's going to be fine.nnWe'll set out to the Withered Tree soon. If you go to Riften, be sure to see Uncle Wilrek.
Find that cave yet? That's our only clue at this point.
Good luck, traveler. Stay well.
Stay well. You don't want what these folks have.
Those cultists were nasty pieces of work. Sure glad Harnald sent you along to help out!
That dragonshrine's always attracted a bad crowd. We'll keep a closer eye on it from now on.
The Peaks' scavengers will feast well tonight!
Don't just stand there gawking. Are you going to help or what?
Kill that Daedroth, or we can't save the Walking City!
Tell me what you found.
Welcome. We're sending all newcomers to check in with Watch Captain Astanya. nnShe's on the docks. Southeast end of the city.
Welcome to Vulkhel Guard. All newcomers must check in with Watch Captain Astanya. You'll find her at the docks on the southeast end of the city.
Who are you, really? Are you here to save us?
Well? Did you find the plans?
Cadwell's a legend among the Soul Shriven. In Tamriel he was mocked and dismissed. Here, he's respected. nnHe's an odd duck, no question, but he knows all the secret paths of Coldharbour.
See what I have seen, traveler. See what the Divines have to show you.
Do I look like I want to talk to you?
Ssk! We are being overrun by a plague of dead giants, a curse of the Worm Cultists.
target: Ssk! We are being overrun by a plague of dead giants, a curse del Culto del Vermeists.

source: So much to do, so much to do. Excuse me, please. Can't let her down.
Good work.
Our friend here was too noisy. Had to have some fun with him. What did the Canonreeve's home yield?
Well? What's your answer? I hope the bodyguards aren't throwing you off. I know they're a little much.
You're quite the clever one. Well done.
Razum-dar wants to say that went pretty well. Then he remembers Fistalle, and her parents.
To allow <<1>> to come to harm would curse this village with the Green Lady's wrath. Please, do what you can to help find her.
At this point some of them will just get clapped in irons when they get back. Every minute slumming around in Vulkhel Guard is three gold off their pay!nnSome of them owe me money now!
Maormer back in the seas around Auridon. No thank you.
I suppose I really should be going now. It's just, Erronfaire's never treated me quite as nicely as spiced rum. And I like to keep myself among friends, if you know what I mean.
Fasarel and the others you've saved give you their thanks, stranger. I'll buy you a round when next we .nnSheor take me. What is that stone you carry?
What? What is it? My guts, still roiling. Damn the sea, and that captain!
Please return as soon as you find <<1>>!
So what have you heard?
Raz must admit. Even he did not think we'd be seeing each other again so soon. How are you, my friend?
Please don't tell Harnald how much you did here. He'll never give me another mission if you do!
<The log sits empty, for now>
New in town, eh? If you're looking to get your feet wet, I have some work needs doing.
Go on ahead. I'll report to Two-Blades as soon as I'm able. Thank you again, my friend.
Please hurry, there isn't much time.
I'll return to Two-Blades when I can. Go on ahead. There may be more lives to save.
Please, master! Mercy on this poor wretch!
That creepy advisor from Mournhold says my father's missing. How is that possible? He's the House Councilor!
Quickly, go fetch Odvild. The poor woman is devastated. This will certainly lift her spirits.
Oh, fair day. Fair day to you. You're here with supplies for Telenger, I expect.nnPlease don't tell him I was sitting down on the job.
I know Cracktooth will come for me. I'm so helpless! What will I do?
You look so proud, what did you find out?
Sorry, but I'm very busy. Please go see Breca at Fallowstone.
Yeah, lots of nice stuff here. I'll just look around while you go find those blades.
I think me and my boy can handle the rest of the chores. nnTruth to tell, I don't think you're cut out for farm work.
Thank Auri-El, a friendly face. You're Raz's cohort, aren't you?
I think the tomb is somewhere within these ice caves.
This is the best party I've been to all night!
Ysmir's beard, it's good to see a friendly face! I never thought I'd find my way out of here.
Ah, good. I was tired of only seeing dead people.
Eshaba has just about anything you could want. So. What can she get you?
Glad you could make it! Talk to Mom, she'll tell you what you need to know.

The King and his parties. Today, three sloppy drunkards wandered into the crypts and haven't been heard from since. nnI'll wager a week's pay they'll unleash something unspeakable down here, and I'll get blamed. They always blame the priest.
Kill the matriarch and this all ends.
Could it be I made the wrong decision?
I can't believe you agreed with him!
Go, go! Let's get out of here.
So  it is the end. There's no saving myself after all.nnMy mother will never forgive me, but I don't regret saving our village. Perhaps I can save her as well.
We'll see that reinforcements reach Firsthold right away. You have the thanks of the Eagles, traveler.
I can hardly believe itEstre, the Veiled Queen.
Good luck with that blade, my friend. Those Heritance bastards are yours.
I don't have words. Thank you so much for finding Ilara. What news of Tanion?
Hmm? Have you had a chance to look around yet?
I've almost recovered enough magicka to assume my disguise. By the time you rescue the Bosmer captives, I'll be ready to go.
I want my drinking horn back! Get it and fill it with my brew, and you and me'll be best buddies.
It's about time. You're heavier than you look.
Greetings, citizen! I seem to have suffered a temporary setback. I require your assistance.
Please let me know if you find Recruit Gorak. He may be a little overzealous, but he means well. nnI think.

We should move on. The design of this altar  it points to the existence of others. There may be more ahead, waiting to be disassembled, and there are still Wood Orcs standing in our way.nnGo on ahead. We'll come to you when you find another altar.

Divines be praised, a friendly face! I've been hiding out here since the Covenant ambushed my team. They took three prisoners. nnI tracked them to a nearby camp. I'd rescue them myself, but there's a slight wrinkle .
Finally, someone with a backbone.
Don't kill me! I'm just a soldier following orders!
They're going to throw me out of the Lion Guard now for sure.
Did Thragof send you? I don't know if we'd have lasted another night out in this cold!
Nurad knows nothing, sees nothing. Leave him be.
Remember: spellcasting all in the timing.
Greetings, brave one. <<1>> has a proposition for you, should you care to hear it.
Here for the Trial of Endurance? This is a race around the island, mind. Not a casual stroll. Think you can handle it?
Start by looking for my runner, Lorumel. She might have learned something. nnWe'll be right behind you, soon as more blades show up. Good luck.
Thank Stendarr, a rescuer! You must help me! They're insane!
There is still much for you to learn.
She's just so glad to be out of that horrid place. Thank you. Thank you for what you did for Ilara.
The curse  it's gone! Indaenir is free! I'm free!
You guessed the old man's riddles and ran a little race. Good for you. Ready for a real challenge?
Thank you for freeing me. It wasn't the choice I would have made, but I appreciate being able to see my son once more.nnI'll do everything I can to make this right.
If you go into the mines, please find my husband Len. I'm terribly worried about him.
I'm going to hurt you very badly.
I heard Dame Clarique let the bandit go into the village. She told us to keep a close watch on anything happening over there.nnI trust the Dame, but I hope we don't regret this.
The captain might've lost more than just his sight, but he's still a pirate at heart.

Did you see the look on their faces? That was the most satisfying moment of my life  or at least this poor excuse for an afterlife in Coldharbour.nnIt's just a pity we couldn't catch a few of the bastards in the rockslide.
Senche-tigers often lie in the small cave near the falls. I often wonder what stories they tell their cubs.
Citizen.
Don't just stand there, help us out!
Well, come on! And put your back into it!
Another Saxhleel? They usually don't let me talk to the others of our kind. What are you doing here?
Get that thing activated. Burn those boats. Save the town.
Go carefully, my friend. The screaming ceased days ago, and now only the wailing and moaning of the undead can be heard from the temple.
I had a feeling the truth would be bad. nnIt's a good thing Urcelmo took a small force with him on ahead. I'd hate for the Queen to have reached the city first. But Rilis. We'll need to warn him.
What a creepy place! I can feel something tugging at my mind.nnFind my brother and the scholars. And hurry! The spell might adapt and eventually trap us in here, too.
I try so hard to resist, but sometimes it's too much. It was easier when Gamirth was here to help me.

As I feared, we arrived in different locations. I am in a city of industry, where men speak of intrigues and plots beneath layers of innuendo and pleasantry.nnIt matters not. You have awakened once again and we must set you on your path.

The members of the Mages Guild compete in the battlegrounds, working with the sides that chose them. You have been granted the rare opportunity to choose your own side, which you must do soon if you wish to aid your friends.nnNow, make your decision.
Did Nelhilda tell you the plan? Did she make something to help us. Oh, tell me that this doomed celebration is finally coming to an end!
Oh dear. What is your type doing here? You smell awful. Truly awful. Get away from me, please.
Let's get back to it.
My poor father. Damn the Daedra!
I have a plan, but I need a crew. Congratulations. You're it. This will go much easier if you follow my orders and agree to do it my way.
You can rely on us.
Well? You got work to do, don't try to chat me up.
Do you think they have gold in Oblivion?nnOh, don't mind me. Just planning for possibilities, you know?
It is a good day to die! Just as long as they don't go for the face, yeah?nnWhen I get to Sovngarde, I want to have all my teeth and hair for the feasting and the warrior ladies.
I can't leave. I can't leave without it!
Look at it. Such terrible beauty.
People need to know about what's happening in the Serk!

I take it that you are the one who read my note? The spells I placed upon it alerted me that non-Daedra eyes examined the writing.nnI do hope that you are a member of the force from Tamriel. If so, I have something to show you.
My husband. I can't find my husband anywhere!
If you can, find my patrol first. They're directly east of here. Somewhere.
Can't a woman drink her mead in peace?
That silly, stupid boy. He's going to get himself killed in there.
Still a bit unsure about what has happened to us, to our little village. But perhaps I'll write a ballad about it one day.
You've chosen to side with us?nnIt was the right decision to make from a list with no good answer. Speak to Angof. You'll see.
Perhaps there is a way to use Thallik's offer of power to our advantage. This one will have to think about this a little more.
Thanks for getting me out of that library. I always tell Kireth to be careful and what happens? I'm the one who gets into trouble!nnMy sister's never going to let me hear the end of this.
I will find this city you speak of and seek you there. Just make sure you remember our agreement.

What an annoying development! The Observer changed the rules! On me!nnMy champion won, so I should be free. Instead, I'm in a cage, waiting for you to make a decision. Clearly, I am the logical choice. Select me and let's be done with this.

Lady Estre appeared. She said I should trust her. That I'd get out of here.nnI  I don't know what to believe, but her words comforted me, at least. That's something. I think I'll stick with her for now.
There you are. I was wondering when you were going to show up and rescue us.nnThe Observer has been so rude. And now he's put me in this cage! What shall I do in here all by myself?
I prayed to the Eight that more help would arrive. And here you are.
Your decision will allow the Hist tree to die with grace and dignity. Please, make An-Jeen-Sakka understand why you chose this path for us.
Don't bother my patrons. They're drinking.
Stay down and keep quiet. You'll reveal my position.
The berries I gave you should lure <<1>> to you, if she's still alive.nnPlease get her before the crocs do!
Good luck with <<1>>. He's a stubborn old Nord.
I hope <<1>> acts quickly. I could do with a good night's rest.
The runner's name is Lorumel. Seek her out. We'll be right behind you, soon as more blades show up. nnGood luck.
Oh Gods, it's you! I knew the damn Worms would just leave me here unguarded!nnPlease, I'm just a librarian. I don't even like the Worm Cult!
You did it, and just in time! The pirates outside the fort didn't notice our arrival.
An attack on the lighthouse? But why? That doesn't make any sense.nnLet me take a look at these plans.
I've begun to distribute the antidote. It will take time, but my people will heal.
Well done, my friend! <<1>> brought me what you found.
I  I don't know how to thank you. And I'm so sorry I insulted you. nnTruly, I'll never forget your kindness!
Thank you again for returning <<1>>. I've run into some unsavory types that would have  taken advantage of the situation.
Lucas was diligent in ensuring no one could discover the keys to that door, but it's possible some Daedra are already on the other side.
My husband awaits you.nnHave no fear, I spoke on his behalf. He won't blame you for the death of his brother.
By Y'ffre's hairy feet, you outsiders just keep showing up!
I'm still not totally clear on what's going on, but I'll help Captain Eilram rally our troops.
Fires of Oblivion! These motherless slavers have captured my entire crew!nnI'm not one to shy away from a fight, but I think I may be in over my head.
I thought running an inn would be safer than sailing a merchant scow. And yet, pirates. Always pirates.
My contact has access to the Mages Guild. If you're not too late, you should find him inside.nnHe has a good nose for what you carry. If you don't find him, he'll find you.
You're with Sai Sahan? Fine, just stay out of my way.
By the Eight, they're everywhere!
Oh, hello. Who might you be? You have a familiar air about you, but I cannot place the face.
Why yes, yes she is.  Thank you for saying so.  You can pass the "Or Step" test case.
You said you'd bring proof of the mine's worth. You should get moving.
This was not how I wanted this to end.
There's little time to stop <<1>>. With <<Ac:2>>, she could control everyone in <<3>>.
Just put your frog in the basket on the end there and they'll be entered in the next race.nnDon't forget to feed them, now!
The feral beasts ruined everything. I don't know how the Bosmer survive out in the wilderness like this. nnLike living in a war without purpose. Savages.
Too busy. Too busy tending Hopper to talk.
Just scoping out the competition. These amphibian idiots are no match for my Snooks.
What? You have no business with me. Begone!
Hey there, do you have a moment?
Been waiting for you. The boss sent me. Need to deal with this Heritance situation, now that you've put Estre in the ground.
Why yes, yes she is.  Thank you for saying so.  You can pass the "Or Step" test case.
This weapon won't forge itself, stranger. I don't have time for idle chatter.
Ah, the hero. What do you want?
I'll be fine. You take care of those bandits!
I don't know how long I'd have waited in that garden if you hadn't come along.
You found <<1>>. Splendid! Simply splendid.
<<1>> is impressed by Pact-soldier's talent and mercy. Now use the keystone to break through <<2>>'s defenses!
Don't get caught tainting their food
<<1>> is pleased to have you at her side.
You can trust Count Hosni, you know. nnEspecially if you're one of his special friends.
Thank the Egg. You made it out too. I think Dracien's gone.

Bakkhara refuses to deal directly with the Orcs.nnWe should finish them and sort out the mess later. But she fears how the Thalmor will react if the Mages Guild raised a hand against a Canonreeve. Even if that Canonreeve is acting on her own.
Did you enjoy your stroll through the Warehouse, little plaything? So many souls, all of them ours. So many thousands of undying soldiers to be crafted to subjugate your planemelded world.
I came here for the gold, but I can't stand here and not bask a little in the history.nnI've often wondered if the Dwemer ever expected they wouldn't be here today.
Please, you must help my family.
Search for the source of the failure. Use the control rod to spur the spider to act. It will do the rest!
Where's <<1>>? Have you seen my wife? You check inside the ship, and I'll sweep the beaches.nnIf he hurt her, I'll raise him from the dead so I can kill him again!
Dead archers are much less effective than live ones. Keep that in mind.
Shalidor found you! Good to see you again. I've deciphered the spell inside the book. Are you prepared for Sheogorath's first test?
An interesting task indeed.
I see the show does not always go on.
Nelanya and the Goblins taken care of in a single stroke. I've found quite the boon in you.nnWe'll handle things from here. You have my thanks.
Have we met? The two of you look familiar.nnNo, I'm fine, I can focus. I'll help the captain stick a cutlass in <<1>>'s throat. Both of them, if I have to.
Don't worry, dearie. Just hop back there and give them what they want. You'll get the hang of it.
Told you chief would say yes! No hurt Byz!
Thank the Green, reinforcements! Where are you coming from?
What can I help you with?
Try not to make too much of a mess.
Come on. Let's go find my sister. Leave Shazah alone too long and you'll find her curled up in a corner with a book.
Help me, please! They've stolen my Iriana.
I think I'll stay out here a while longer, since this is as close to him as I'll ever get.
I do beg your pardon, but would you happen to be amongst the living? Everything is so hazy.nnOh, I'm talking to another corpse, aren't I? Damn my ghostly eyes!
Quickly, my new friend. Speak to Khali. We're in agreement. The signs are all there. You may yourself have an important role to play in the Two-Moons Dance.
Throw that switch, please.
Great. A fan.nnI need you to keep quiet!
I fear Sir Hughes may already be too far gone. May the Eight watch over his soul.
Mother said this would happen. I can't do anything right.
Chief Tazgol is leading the Orcs toward Carzog's. He's determined to wipe the Bloodthorn Cult off Betnikh.
Ugh. Whatever she was doing felt like a giant hand crushing my skull! I could not have lasted much longer.
Here he comes. He has no idea, does he?
This is so exciting!
Not a bad look for you! The Drublog down by the waterfront won't notice a thing.nnYou'd better get moving while the magic's fresh.
The festival is so much fun!
You've brought the parts?
How's the wine downstairs? Did you find the special blend?
If we don't get those civilians out, they'll be sitting ducks for the Drublog.nnI've heard this particular Wood Orc clan likes nothing better than to torment the helpless.
Khajiit is flattered the goblins would try to eat him.nnThanks.
My crew's safe and only a little bit tortured. I call that a win!
Looks like those four totems hold <<c:1>> captive. If my father told the truth, what you carry can disrupt them.nnI'll protect you any way I can, but I won't raise a hand against my own clan.
The future of the Drublog is uncertain. As my daughter always said, I must learn to think for myself.
I knew you were champion material.
I hoped we could duel.
Behold! You stand before the great one.
It's time to see how tough you really are.
You've done this before. Touching him should draw you into the dream.
There are no lies on the battlefield. Shall we find your truth?
Look for the entrance to Bloody Bhosek's dungeon beneath the palace. And watch your step.
If I smack you around too much, feel free to cry. I love it when they cry.
Now, answer my question. What are you doing here?
Do you think I'm an idiot? I just watched you give that moron his pouch of moon-sugar candy!
You're ready now? Wait. There's a giant over there!
Go kill the werewolf and get the bucket for Jill.
I really need that bucket.
Be careful, good-looking.
Do me a favor and keep the lucky pouch between you and me  yes?
Greetings, Champion.
I can't wait to tell my uncle I met you. Count At-Tura speaks very highly of you. nnGood luck in Gavaudon. Kill an ogre for Captain Ernele while you're out there!
Rama's family, so I'm sure you'll understand if I don't cooperate with his execution. nnJust, pleasemake it quick.
It's not over yet. Please, you have to win! They mean to feed me to these monstrosities!
What did you decide to do with the relic?
Thanks to you, we've actually got a chance to pull this off.
Destroy the relic, now! Didn't you hear the screams, as those things consumed the souls of my people?
It's in the box. You open it by moving the lid. You know, with your hands.
So you know about Nanwen.
Fancy a tune while you scrub the floors?
Ah my friend, come in and relax.
Khali  why? Damn that Javad Tharn to Oblivion!
I'm very glad you're in there keeping him out of trouble. I swear, sometimes I feel more a nursemaid than a scholar. Hah!
Go  Hallowed. Get her out of here.
Looks like the plan was a success. And Gloo said you helped to evacuate some of the villagers?
Go ahead. Light the crates. She'll talk.
Hey, there you are! I remembered what you weren't supposed to do. nnBut you still have both your hands, so obviously you didn't do it!
I knew Captain Kaleen would get another crew together! When she wants something, she gets it!
Again, sailors flock to the Spearhead. For this, Kasan is thankful.
You will always find a warm welcome aboard our ship, for as long as Captain Kaleen's in charge.
Hey, when's the next high tide?
We must stop the cultists before their efforts bear fruit, to the ruin of us all.
Ahh, good choice, partner. Your cunning has made us a lot of coin.
You would desecrate our relics for the sake of coin. You sicken me.
Milk Eyes is a kind old man. You will see. If he says there are rats, I'm sure there are rats. Be sure to tell him I say "bright moons".
Have you delivered the <<1>>s to the bar?
You've returned. What happened? Where is the Queen's agent?
Offerings to the gods are best made in a timely manner. Please hurry.
Be very careful how you speak to her, assistant. We're in her web. We need to tread lightly.
Keep your voice down. Tazia has no interest in slavery today, thank you.
What a rotten day.nnThe entire Merethic Society collection is stored in these ruins. And the Worm Cult gets to have their way with it all.
I just need to gather my strength and hobble back to town. Get that Goblin king and bring me his crown, if you can!
It would seem that the Captain's concern for me was well founded.nnYou saved me from this assassin's blade, as well as from my own foolishness this day.
You have my thanks just for seeking that Rakhad. Shuzura thought him a noble Khajiit. But instead he is a snake in the grass.
Well done, very well done. Now take the circlet  and get ready.
This one hopes you can help Milk Eyes with his rat problem. Ezzag wants to find more than his old bones next time he goes for cards.
And what might you want?
I know I was bound for Daggerfall when my ship was attacked. I need to find a way there.
Can't hardly keep my eyes open. I hope I don't bleed out before I can get back to <<1>>.nnDid you find the plant?
Would you hurry up and bring me the item??
If the Pact leaves us alone, they are welcome to Drakelowe Keep.
What's all this, then?
Seems we've you to thank for <<1>> and the lieutenant's return.nnJone and Jode shall dance with you, wherever you may roam!
If you choose to destroy the relic, then you've turned your back on me and the Covenant.
Thank you for your service. By the time you're done gathering those samples, I'll be back up in the camp. Look for me there.
Good day. This one is on royal business. If you will excuse
You're back! I knew you'd make it.
This was part of a larger plan. I'm sure of it!
You're the one who discovered what the Bloodthorn are planning?nnI'm impressed. Now go help kill them.
I need to get <<1>> out of here. Thanks to you, were going to have to find another way to heal his sickness.

When I heard my brother had fallen ill, I was extremely concerned. We've had troubles in Alcaire, but nothing this bad.nnAll the same, I'm glad to hear he's all right, and I understand I have you to thank for it.nnThank you.
Judging by that sickening smell, you got some of Zich's food.
Stay away from me, you foul beast.
Do you always fall for such sob stories?nnWell, I think it's a fool's errand, but be careful out there.
You've done well, but I need you to talk to <<1>> about getting more of the people on our side.
This is a disaster. The bastards were prepared for us.
I was a fool, an arrogant, overconfident fool. I should have listened to them all.
We're preparing to climb to the summit. Destroy the other Conduit Stones and meet us there.
Those damn Redguards! Showed up and made me move from the warm spot I had by the river!nnI may be poor, but a little respect would be nice.
These were the Five Companions, who set out from the Imperial City on an epic quest to recover the lost Amulet of Kings.
All of us feel the light of the Bright Moons on our faces with the Hallowed walking the halls of Do'Krin.
If I get turned into an undead monster, feel free to crush my skull. Seriously. I never want to be like that.
Tell me what you found.

Honor to you. Three keystones must be activated to unseal the entrance to the inner ruins of Moriseli. You'll find them ahead. nnBe cautious. The air reeks of foul necromancy. Powerful magic taints the very ground.
What's my brother talking about? How did he fail us? You need to talk some sense into him!

I wish this victory didn't feel so hollow. Other than keeping the undead at bay, it seems there's little we can do to battle this darkness.nnWe are here to support you and Indaenir though, if you need us. Are you going to rejoin him now?
I trust you will make wise decisions.
I think the Forge-Wife's bite is much worse than her bark. Seriously, her tusks are huge.
Hey friend. Care to have a drink? nnYou'll have to buy though. I'm flat broke. Can't even pay my debts. Have to go upstairs and tell S'rashi I don't have his money . You think he'll have me killed?
Steel and stone, another mainlander?  At least you don't look like a good puff from the bellows would knock you over.
Your defeat will honor the Seamount clan.
Come to try your luck with me?
I see Talmo's Aldmeri banner. I hoped you would destroy it.
The Bright Moons will guard your path!
If you do the hunting, I'll do the cooking. I promise you won't regret helping me beat <<1>>!
There's something moving in there. Help me get it open.
I understand the Orcs want you to prove our worth through combat?  How depressingly typical of their kind.
What a fortunitious event, meeting you here! I hope your hunting went well.
When I recover completely, I'll leave this place and start over.
I don't know what I'll do without that lute. I've been a musician since childhood.
Troubled times in Glenumbra, it seems. All I hear is bad news no matter where I turn.nnBut the worst, as far as I'm concerned, is poor Crosswych.
You're not considering keeping that thing, are you? It'd take all the fun out of war.
An intriguing place, the Valley of Blades. It'll be a treat to see where Sai Sahan trained as a boy.
This is a great moment! You will assist me in the study of this object, won't you?
Do you have the poison gas? Quickly now, give it to me.
First you appear out of nowhere, and now this! What are you anyway?
We'll hold here. Keep moving.
Continue on your path. We have your back.
We should get started with the clean-up as soon as possible.
The destructive act unleashes their corporeal form, yes? Untethers them from Nirn. The attunement Esan has put on the Fang draws forth power from that tether, harnesses it for our needs.
I really need those mushrooms. Five should do for now.
I meet you at last. I saw you defeat the scheming Redguard who rules Stros M'Kai. I see great events swirling about you.
So the fighting's over? I guess that means everything's back to normal now, right?nnNot for me.
I didn't expect an outsider to be of any help. I am indebted to you.
You have done it. All that remains is to claim the Claw.
You are a bright moon in Felari's sky. Thank you. You can find Nethrin recovering in the tavern. He's beside himself with worry.
Welcome aboard. I have interesting news. <<1>> has asked us for a favor. He has another problem he'd like us to resolve.
We  we did it. We walked the path and lived. I'm  I'm going to be the Mane. And my sister is dead.
The Dominion has never known a greater hero. And I am proud to call you a friend.
Your bravery astonishes me, Hallowed. To my ears this Path you walk sounds like some kind of nightmare.
Our thoughts are with you, Hallowed. May the Green guide your steps.
The hopes of my people go with you, Hallowed.
The wardstones surround the grove. They are powered by magicka.
Traveler! A moment if you please. I'm an  associate of Cariel's. Would you have a moment to assist me? My horse startled as we crossed the bridge, and I lost some important cargo over the side.
Three servants reunited to their master. Only one remains.
Well  that hurt .
Move on down the river, friend. I'm mulling my next wager. There is much profit to be made at the arena!

If what Razum-dar says is true, the city of Woodhearth owes you a debt. Of course, if the city's attacked and destroyed, that won't be worth much. Maybe we can prevent that.nnThe cat said you found orders from Vicereeve Pelidil. Can I see them?
If you're leaving soon, I'd like to ask a favor of you.
If you are fortunate enough to actually speak to the Wilderking, I suggest you keep the conversation to yourself.nnOtherwise, people might think your brain's turned to peat moss.
I'm glad you're here. We were worried we'd missed our opportunity. The other scouts report that Fildgor's flank is undefended.
May the light of the Bright Moons wash you in their purity. May you bathe in moonlight, and let it suffuse your soul.
Who's there? I didn't kill your Dominion friends. I warned them, but they didn't listen.
Beat three of my hunters in duels and my axe is yours.

I wonder if you know how completely we are in your debt? Alik'r warriors fear no evil, but they will not fight the undead.nnIt may be a superstition, but it has been tradition for centuries. I could not have convinced my guards to break it today.
By the Eight, you've got one of the skulls! And you don't appear to have fallen under the spell . nnLet me see it. Please!
His hunters? Ha! The Hunt-Wife better not hear him talking like that!
Something's wrong. He smells  very dead.
Not another one. Where does Garnikh find you suckers?
Yeah? I don't have all day.
We should head up to the gates to the keep. It won't hurt to check in on the King, though I doubt anyone without a key could get past those gates.

My hope is that Prince Azah might have a lead on where Uwafa and Alasan have set up their headquarters, or better yet, what they're planning next.nnRegardless, these are things we should discuss at the palace.
Those supply caches are the runners' only chance to reach help. We must get them stocked!
I know that many aren't happy you kept the relic, but you made the right decision.nnIf you're ever in trouble, you can call on my blade. I hope we get the chance to sail together again, my friend.
Move along. Don't you have somewhere to be?
Sithis? Here? That can't be .
Hallowed, I can see the light of the Dance reflected in your eyes. Jone and Jode smile down upon you now. They are with you, at this difficult hour. You must choose.

As you've just seen, the young girlAraniasis associated with the Veiled Heritance. Until I know more about her, I hesitate to call her an enemy.nnI will have more insight soon though. Even now, Aranias is on her way to my throne.
I heard what she said. She's a good friend, Bowenas. Must be very hard for her.
What I propose is simple. A kind of limited partnership. Kill <<1>> and walk out of here with that boy Tand.
My life mate must have been sick with worry. I never thought I would see Sind again. This one doesn't deserve him.
This one begs your indulgence. He wonders if you have seen a flaxon-furred Khajiit with a braided mane in your travels?
Well met, friend. I don't suppose you have seen a male Khajiit wandering about? He has mane-braids like mine, and a foolish tendancy to gamble until his pockets are empty.
I can see the benevolence of S'rendarr in your eyes. Thank you.
Let's see how tough your guardian is. Go to the stumps to pit your guardian against the others. You can use the stone to heals yours if you like.

So you commanded the general to turn around and fight on our behalf instead?nnI feel sorry for the spirits of his soldiers that they remain bound here, but at least you were able to free the villagers from the Shadow Wood.
You've returned! nnI hope you have fared better in your travels than I. For a moment I imagined you were a Daedric illusion. Rilis and his Daedric thrall have been a menace to me.
The hero of the caravan returns! Are you in for the next race? We have many fine and juicy lizards!
Ah, freedom at long last! My calculations suggested that you had a slightly better chance to fail rather than to succeed. I suspect, though, that you often beat the odds. Thank you.
Ah, look around you. See how the people brighten the streets with their very presence! It is good to have this place inhabited once again.
Admit it. You cannot resist the lure of the spikeball!
Find out what he wants. We need to get out of here!
This isn't going to be a happy reunion, but don't worry  I won't overstep my bounds.
There you are! Quick as you please. There's even time for tea.
With the Elder Scroll of Mnem in our hands once again, the Dominion is greatly strengthened.
Go. Go and find whoever did this to her. They must pay.
I hope that helmet does the trick. If that doesn't put her in a more reasonable state of mind, we may have to turn to a more forceful solution.
Ezreba awaits judgment. This one is ready to face the consequences of her actions. She hopes that mercy remains in the hearts of her neighbors.
Make no threats within <<1>>. You've been warned.
The Shadowscales aren't currently providing gifts, but speak ill of us we'll gift you with a thrashing.
I was very proud of this meal, too. Damned cultists.
Dancing elves, forest spirit kings  these people are pulling on the tail in more ways than one.nnYou can stay if you want to, but Hazazi thinks it is time for him to return to Marbruk.
You have better things to do than spend time talking to me, outsider.
Is that Captain Arakh's helmet? Well, return it to her already! She's about to rush us!
Our hero honors this humble arena! These troll fights are nothing compared to your fearsome battle with the great <<1>>. This one has already heard several tavern songs about it.
With the mist no longer claiming our hunters, Longhaven will thrive again, thanks to you. nnMake yourself at home! Doralin makes an excellent brew if you've the stomach for it.
I will speak to you ahead, when you have solved solved the riddle.
<It appears that a gem would fit within the face of this statue.>

Well aren't you the bold one? Running around this part of the forest, you've got to be either fearless or just plain foolhardy.nnHaven't you seen the undead? I'm a Vinedusk Ranger and I'm not even sure I'm safe here.
<It appears that a gem would fit into the face of this statue.>
<It appears that a gem would fit into the face of this statue.>
The sight of their kinsmen's blood on your axe ought to loosen our prisoners' tongues.
Begone, pig child.
Even if the rest of the townsfolk don't want to think about it, having atronachs roaming about is bad news.
We've gathered the prisoners' belongings. A quick search may give you clues to what they know.nnMake these Bretons talk, Targoth, or the blood of your people is on your head.
It's hard to think of life in Greenhill without her, but I agree. The villagers cannot live with a traitor in their midst.
Been thinking. If I were bigger, waves would've smashed me even harder. Punctured lung, cracked skull?nnNever thought being this short would come in handy.
We'll make sure the Sea Vipers don't attack the Prowler. Make them suffer.
Gods be with you.
Lots of snakes out here. Watch your ankles.
You do see that I have a bow, don't you?
Back off. I don't have any interest in speaking to your kind.
I won't be able to sleep until that Dremora is dead.
It's done, isn't it? <<1>> is sealed inside with that monster.
We've restored the Mourning Stone. But if you're here, then <<1>> is lost to that monster.
The Sea Vipers are prowling around the beach, stealing our supplies. Do you know how hard we worked to liberate those crates from Covenant sloops?nnStinking fish-Elves.
This is rather disconcerting. I don't believe I've ever had a conversation with a monkey before.

I know going against Kaleen was a hard thing. It was for me as well. We have more history together than you can imagine.nnEven so, I'm leaving. It's time to start my own crew, sail my own ship. You, my friend, would be welcome with us anytime.

I wish I could have retrieved that Ayleid relic for study, but you were wise to destroy it rather that place it in Breton hands.nnI realize Kaleen disagrees with your decision, but never doubt it was the right one.

I know the others have doubts, but that's their problem.nnIf Captain Kaleen believes the power of that relic can be used for good, I do too. You did the right thing! When I see my brothers again, I'll tell them what you did for them.

By destroying the relic, you have saved the world from a great evil. Kasan's apprentice does not agree, but she has lost her way. This one can only hope she one day returns to the true path.nnGo safely, friend.
Don't hurt me. You can have the coin I've earned so far. For my debt.
You made it past the undead outside Marbruk? Either that, or I lost more blood than I thought.
My favorite traveler! The forest keep and protect you on your path.

Killing <<c:1>> was foolish. <<A:2>> and <<c:1>> shared a lifebond. She has little time to avenge him before she too will die, and <<c:2>> is a most dangerous creature.nnBut then, you have that spring in your stride again. What have you learned?
You recovered our eggs! How wonderful! My people will be most grateful to you for this.
Good luck in there. Hopefully, the Stonefire haven't been able to finish their ritual.
Bright moons guide you and watch over the Mane in his darkest hour.
I warned them. Warned them! But why would I know anything about Maormer treachery?nnMaybe now they'll listen to reason. It only takes a murder, right?
You heard <<1>>'s story. If the Sea Vipers call up another hurricane before the tide rises, the Prowler will be smashed to pieces.

Your pardon, friend. The Dominion's arrival on <<1>> has upset the locals. It falls on me to smooth the waters.nnPlease, help yourself to food or drink. I'm happy to speak with you once this matter is settled.
Even our worst enemies deserve respect. I admit, I'm glad to be proven wrong about Dominion justice.
Never thought I'd be so grateful to be cleaning the house. Hah.
I have some questions for this pompous lackwit of a vicereeve. Do let me know if you find any leads, won't you?
Stop her so I can kill her!

Balag welcomes you! If you are cunning of mind and fierce of spirit, Thizzrini Arena is the place to prove these things! nnAlso, Balag is running short of competitors. It is the downside to running fights to the death.
You again? Don't tell me you were serious about competing in the Sorcerer Division Championship. You'll be eaten alive!
You're a strong one, aren't you? Are you ready for a real challenge?
You still breathe, and your lovely face is intact. Zara is very pleased. And yet, she is also sad.
"Mysterious Stranger." I like the sound of that. Fight well and you could be the arena's next star!

I've never met the Wilderking, but I'm sure he wouldn't have created a bunch of monsters to indiscriminately kill innocent Bosmer. nnEither way, my people have sacrificed enough already. We're staying here, even if that means we do so as corpses.
Ah, the pain! It's exquisite! But this has to end.nnThe Great Mage must be made whole again so we can finish our mission!
Been a kwama master for over a decade. I'm not afraid to admit when I'm up to my neck in droppings, and I sure could use a hand getting out.
Have you seen <<1>>? He's missing.
Get off my ship before I throw you off.
<<1>> depends on the Great Tree, yet it sickens before my eyes. Our fates are like leaves in its branches.

You have now witnessed the first sacrifice, and you know that true honor need not be named.n nYou are now one of us. You are Ash'abah.  We will recognize you as our brother and together, we will uphold the sacred duty of our tribe.
Come, let us see how the Wood Elves' council fared against my children.
What did my father say? Did you convince them?
Now is the time to strike. <<1>> must die for his crimes.
This is a dreadful place. Kargand appreciates your assistance.
We have to find the Engine. If we disable it, the ruins will be safe to explore.
This is horrible. The spirit wasn't any help. The Great Tree can't last much longer against the vapor!
Marimah says you are to become an Ash'abah, so I welcome you to our tribe.nnTrue honor need not be named.

Have you come to look over our books concerning the undead? Word has reached us that a blight has emerged from the waters surrounding the docks. I'm afraid our library doesn't contain any relevant literature, but please look over my other goods.
You are welcome to our camp. nnWe are usually generous hosts, but  under the circumstances, I hope you understand.
Hail and welcome, comrade. How goes the fight?
What did I ever do to that Netch?

The trial is over. <<1>> found my companions guilty and sentenced them to death. They were taken to the cells below the hall while preparations are made for the execution.nnI'm working on a distraction to cover our escape. Did you find the key?

Where did you come from? <<1>> will take a look at you. Hmm, no injuries this one can see, and very dry for a castaway.nnYou hit your head in the shipwreck, yes? You should stand on one foot. We must be certain.
I didn't expect to be treating Dominion soldiers so soon. That hurricane came out of nowhere.nnAnd who might you be? Up from the shore with not a scratch on you!
He's got to be hiding it around here somewhere. I can smell it. Keep looking.
Oblivion's sake, another clueless jackass. I'm hung over and bored. What?
I find your antics to be quite enticing, little mortal!
The flame is lit! Before I fade forever, you must burn the tomes!
Damnable Daedric rituals. Just wait until I'm free.
Nice to be out of that ogrim trash pit. nnI'm ready to take on Molag Bal himself now!
Marvelous, isn't it? We'll have to construct a special room for <<Ac:1>> when we bring it back to the Mages Guild.nnI'm sorry, did you need something?
Trapped in Coldharbour  my squad scattered  some kind of commander I am.
They did not cover this in training.
Welcome to <<1>>, friend. The hurricane must have been very disorienting. So many injured, confused  keep your voice down. Try not to draw attention.
Azsu will remember this. Oh, yes.
Ah, well. <<1>> bears no grudge, and wishes you luck in your endeavors.nnProvided they involve no more burning of books.
At ease, soldier. Fresh from the wreck? You've got a faraway look about you.nnIf you feel unwell, I'd suggest visiting <<1>>.
You must do what we Hollow cannot.
Clever, luring <<cm:1>> out of their mounds like that. A scheme worthy of Baan Dar, himself!nnThey're all gone, then?
Quick! Kill him!
Father burned in the fire, my brother missing  S'rendarr, show mercy!
This one found a sugar-rat you roasted. It was dipped in <<cm:1>> egg yolk. How was <<2>> to resist?nnSo delicious! But  so sleepy .
Bright moons, you have saved Akkhuz-ri. Drove out the evil that was corrupting his soul. Thanks to you, Akkhuz-ri is free.
Hurry! Find the key and let us out of these damn cages, yes?
I never expected to have to do battle with Daedra! I rather enjoyed myself!
That was too close for comfort! I'm a conjurer, not a battle mage!nnAnyway, thanks for getting us out of those cages. I appreciate it.
This one must gather the strength to end Kargand's corruption.
Go ahead at get started on the slab. I'll walk you through the process.
You have given us much to consider, outsider. Please return to the Moonless Walk. We shall come to you after a decision has been reached.
You think the others were a challenge? Wait until you face Ishalga in the arena!
Bring the seeds back to Laniriel. I must go to the Fading Tree, and only Caretakers may set foot there.
I asked around. Nobody from the shipwreck remembers seeing you before <<1>>.nnNo more lies! You're running skooma, aren't you?
Please, my family has seen enough pain today. Do what is right.
There's too many of the foul beasts! We can't get close to those focus stones.
No, no! I'm too late. Erunor, you oathbound fool! Let me in!nnDamn it! He must not be able to hear me behind this barrier.
Well done.
Good day, traveler. Mind yourself around these parts.
The Goddess watch over and keep you in your search. You seek four of Mara's treasures: a circlet, a dagger, a phylactery, and  of course  the chalice.
Damned Dremora are defending those stones. Already took out a few of our people. They'll pay for that! I promise you!
You must be the latest of Captain Balrook's playthings. You're certainly his type.
There is nothing like practice for perfecting one's skills, yes?
This one is at one with Jone and Jode.
It's too late to change our minds now. Destroy those binding totems and leave us to our work!
You've done it, Hallowed. The Champions have stepped onto their new path. And all that remains is to conclude the ritual.
Quickly, now! Your lives are on the line, too, you know.
Please. I honor your commitment to the Pact, but I have no more time for chat.
If you're done here, time to move along, warrior.
So, now you're a siege weapon master, eh? Well, battle will tell.
Now we must return to the Harvest Heart. There is one more thing to do before we can destroy Molag Bal's vile monstrosity.
Khali  she does not look so well. What happened in there?
Shazah doesn't look like her usual upbeat self. Is she all right?
I never expected that reversing the conduits would cause that poor creature to explode. Ah, well. Live and learn.nnThis door leads to the Great Mooring. We're almost there!
They can't do this! We've got to get rid of them!
I wonder if they will notice if I wrap this tree around myself and hide.
Have a seat by the fire and let me know when you're ready to hear the story. Remember, ask nicely.
What I wouldn't give to be having this meeting in Skyrim. It's hot as dragon's breath in here.
If anyone can get to the bottom of this, it's you and Aelif. She's gone up to the roof of the Hall to get some air. Stendarr guard your steps, my friend.
I cannot believe we are still standing here! nnPlease, talk to Enneh and then let me know what he says. If he doesn't know where Casnar is, then we can call the wedding off!
This path is over, but the journey never ends. May the moons shine brightly on you in the future.
By the shining trees of Aldmeris. We have been burgled, but how?
Shh. Keep one good ear to the ground, always.
Hazazi never thought he would miss the dancing Bosmer.
Oh! Ah  greetings, traveler. What can I do for you?
What have you learned of my old friend, <<1>>?
Thank the gods you're here!
By the forest itself, I'm saved! Thank you. Did Nethrin send you?
The portal. It's unsealed? Praise the Divines. And Galandir? Is he all right?
Looks like we only meet in horrible places! Did you bring the hundred blades this time?nnNo matter. You didn't need them in Firsthold.
I've seen no sign of a forest spirit so far, ancient or otherwise. But there is, indeed, a powerful aura about this place.

I wasn't expecting open war out here, but that's what that was. Patraud never had a chance.nnI don't know what the Warlock has gotten us into, but I'll die fighting if I have to. I'm Redguard before I'm a Mage.
Warlock Carindon may trust you, but that doesn't mean I do. I've no desire to have my fate dictated by the likes of you.
This is difficult to behold, but if it saves another mage from harm, then I'll abide it.
The price of knowledge is always high, but I don't like the feel of this place. Mayhem awaits us, I think.
Don't worry, I'm not dead yet. Go on. I'll see you around.
Remember, only the best and most delectable bones for I.

This continued aggression from the Bosmer is distressing. With two mages lost already, we'll need to be careful. My fallen colleagues will not be forgotten.nnNo doubt our elusive forest spirit is nearby.
How dare you enter our gathering hall, you Crown dog! Go back to your own kennel for jackals!
You have a senche-tiger's heart coming here, Crown. But the bravery of a beast is rooted in folly. Leave now.
Forebear dog! Do not sully our carpets with your faithless heels. Leave now.
I'll  I'll see you back in Rawl'kha. Go  go now. Save Lorwen!
Welcomeit's good to have you come with us. You will not find that cup of fellowship in that Forebear Magistrate's hall.
I I feel like I've been through this before. Thanks for helping me. I couldn't have fought them off alone.nnLet's get back to the manor. I'm getting hungry.
Those are the items I seek! Give them to me, and I will learn their place in the story of my people.

I believe it's best to destroy the focuses first. Alasan's minions have been piling the dead around them, and they seem to be channeling energy for the ritual.nnDestroy the focuses; then go to the lighthouse and find a way to disrupt Alasan's ritual.
Ah good  you're here. Razum-dar was afraid he would have to bleed to death by himself.

Send another score and I will smite them just the same! I could cut down Sea Vipers all day long!nnWell done, my friend! We'll have the sanctuary back under control quickly now, but we can't stop here. The battle's only just begun!
My soul! They've taken my soul!

I'm glad there are a few of us left who know the meaning of courage and loyalty! You'd make High King Emeric proud.nnLook on the decks of the three ships. The designs should be there  unless they've already been stolen!
Her body must be consecrated, or the gods will know her not.
Have a seat by the fire and let me know when you're ready to hear the story. Remember, ask nicely.
Hurry up. I ain't getting any younger.
You have returned! This one hopes the visions were not too intense. Raz has heard stories.
It's good to finally meet you. I'm very happy we could be here to support Akkhuz-ri and the Champions. This is a vulnerable moment for our fragile new Dominion.
Good luck in there.
I have heard of your valor, though we have not met before. My Silvenar and I are well pleased that we could be here to support the Khajiiti people.
Green keep you. This is my first time on the borderlands of Valenwood. And my first time in a Khajiiti temple! I'm honored to be here today.

The path never ends, my friend. We must always walk forward and pray that the moons will guide us to where we should go. Now I must rebuild this city and my people. Restore the physical body of the Khajiit and the spiritual body of my people.
Some things are best left undisturbed.
Hey there mortal! How you doing?
The story now approaches its conclusion. There will be a reckoning for Aranias and for the Wilderking himself.nnYou must hasten to Greenheart, for you still have a key role to play.

If the Eldest has been corrupted, then everything in this areaevery plant, every creature, and every person will soon become corrupted as well.nnI can't imagine how this blight can so easily penetrate the forest's protections.
Nnnn! It's  just barely holding together!
Quickly. Aranias waivers. She knows now why she was guided herenot to destroy the Valenwood, but to save it.nnShe wants to change course, but she's afraid. She's afraid to stand up to Andur.

It's you ? From Silatar? My  my friend. Thank the Eight! You were right about the Veiled Heritance. I'm sure now. nnThey used me as bait to trick the Wilderking, and now Andur's going to kill him. I can't let that happen. I have to stop Andur.
It's you! And Lyris! What are you doing here?
I saw you talking to <<1>>. I hope he's finally going to do something about these ruffians and thieves.
You've returned! Don't try to interfere. Pircalmo brought this on himself. Atronachs! In our wood!
I don't know what <<1>> plans to do about these bandits, but I hope he does it soon.
What's going on? Where's Pircalmo? Where's my husband?
Another damned bandit? Oblivion take you, I have no more supplies to give you, filth.
You look weary. Perhaps you'd care to stop here and rest? We have much to offer.
My dueling lessons have finally paid off. We made it down here with almost no trouble. Well, <<1>> helped a little.nnDid you find Lady Laurent's jewels?
You look so tense! You need to relax. Please, enjoy our hospitality and let all your worries slip away.
Did it work? Yes, I can see it in your eyes! Now you can see things as they really are.
I'm half a heartbeat from throwing you out of this camp.
What?

After you receive your briefings from Hahnin and Gabrielle, select a soldier to accompany you on your mission. Choose carefully, for our plan hinges on you opening the way into the Labyrinth.nnThis is our last strike. Make it count.

I have seen more than my fair share of years. Many more. But in all that time, I've never contemplated something as foolhardy as this.nnWe're about to face a Daedric Prince for the fate of our world, and I couldn't be more proud of all of you.
What are you waiting for? Kill that horrible creature already!
Welcome, Moon Hallowed. Welcome to your first steps along the path.

I'm a brilliant artificer and a genius when it comes to Dwemer constructs. But I have to tell you, being surrounded by all these remarkable men and women . It's kind of humbling.nnI hope I live long enough to record this in my posterity journal.
This one cannot wait to see what's inside the stronghold of the Daedric Prince!nnBut Zur wishes that Gadris was here to share this auspicious occasion.

I imagined that this was going to be a grand adventure, but I never pictured the horror of all this.nnSo many of our friends and companions have died, and this damn vortex still threatens our world. I think it's time we shut it down. Permanently.

I see you there, but you must wait. A scholar's work is seldom urgent, but I have a request from the king himself. It seems the Ansei Wards have been misplaced! nnWait, I should not have . Um, just forget I said that.
Hurry! If you take too long, these Ungodly might decide to kill me. Find those keys!
I'm afraid you'll have to pardon me. I'm here on royal business.
Don't talk to me. I have problems. Big problems.nnYou wouldn't understand.
We did it. It was an honor to fight beside you once again. We've certainly come a long way from the Temple of the Mourning Springs, don't you think?
How much gold did you take from my daughter's dowry? How full are your pockets, you snake?
My soldiers stir from their feral state. I can only assume the corruption has receded, and Naemon is again put to rest.
At last! Sai Sahan has been taken to the Halls of Torment!
Come. I need to speak with Queen Ayrenn. I expect she'll want to speak with you as well.

Now here's one who I know is loyal to the king! It's good to see you again, my friend.nnYou're going to find this hard to believe, but the damned Imperials are here! They've seized control of the cityfor the moment, at least.
I'll be with you in a moment.
You're back! You stopped <<1>>, then?nnOh, no. <<2>> didn't survive, did she?
You keep returning like some kind of scale-rot. Leave me be, outsider.
Praise Meridia! This one was worried he'd never find another living soul in this horrible place.
She is wounded! Did you hurt her?
We have to find out what they're doing.
We've got some repairs to do on the Prowler, but maybe we'll sail together again soon. Until then, stay safe.
We should check the houses, or secluded areas with good visibility of the quay.
Survivors of the Sea Viper attack will likely have hidden. Perhaps the buildings around <<1>>?

I knew we could do it! We're practically on Molag Bal's doorstep now!nnMolag Grunda is no more. At least for now. Daedra don't really die, if my studies are correct. But at lease she's out of our way for now.
Tu'whacca has taken the Chief beyond the dunes. So passes Marimahwater into sand. May all the Divines bless his passage.
We mustn't dally. Naemon's Shade and his servants clearly have larger, darker designs. nnWe should spread out and search for signs of their corruption and do our best to stamp it out wherever we can.
I think  I think I just narrowly missed Tu'whacca's summons, sister. I credit my mother. She had a stomach like an iron kettle.
Still alive, are you? And all your limbs intact? Maybe you should spend more time adventuring and less time at the tavern. Ha!
The old Fighters Guild Hall. It's near the main gate. Go!
We were able to overcome the vampiric snare of the Orchard. I expect we'll handle the Reaver Citadel with equal aplomb.
We have come so far, but we have leagues to go before this business is concluded.nnWe must push forward! We must find a way through the walls of the fortified city that looms ahead of us.
As I was saying, there's a blight here. I'd highly advise staying away.

Thank you, traveler. The barkeep in the Waxing Crescent Inn  I think his name was Duzal-ja? He has one of them, and can probably tell you where to look for the others. We have to get the relics back before Meldil makes an appearance.

Phenomenal. I knew proximity was the key! And look at you, not even a hint of electrocution.nnYou have the principle. Now, to apply it to the other <<m:1>> before  well, best not to worry you about that.
I know why you originally came hereto ask for the Wilderking's allegiance to the Aldmeri Dominionto know the Valenwood was on your side.nnWould you still make such a request to me now?
I can't believe <<1>> let me stay like this. Come, let's help the old bones drive back the new!
We're almost free! Only one task remains.nnYou must die.
Let's go!
I already told youI'm not going anywhere!nnThe Taskmasters in this place  they can inflict pain that should killbut doesn't. I will not risk getting strung up by them! Not even to escape!
I didn't think we'd survive this day. Many have died, but some live.nnThank you for fighting on our behalf.
You've returned, and this one heard fighting.nnCould  Taskmaster be dead?
The Eight take this thing! Everyone's going to think I'm a thief. An incompetent thief!
Auri-El watch over you. Maybe just tell Malesse my Tacia is adopted? And that I don't want her to feel unwelcome here? I don't know. I don't understand that woman.
Welcome, welcome. We have  lots of interesting people here. Like the merchant, Sarolion. He's certainly got a story or two.
I'm the operations manager for the Summoner Division. I assume you've earned your credentials?
Drauginor's the name. Business manager for the Sorceror Division. Credentials, please.
Zara's tasked me with picking flowers, believe that? I'm a swordsman, not a flower girl! nnDamn my tongue, I can't say no to that girl. It's that purr of hers. Damned distracting.
I see you were successful.
We all saw the corruption draw back. It's such a relief.
This one is relieved to see such estimable help arrive. Raz has already volunteered to enter Hectahame himself, but the queen has forbidden it.
Quite an amazing scene to witness.

It's good to see Akkhuz-ri made it out safe and sound. Gharesh-ri tried to warn him of the danger, but he doesn't always listen. He sometimes forgets he's a spiritual leader and not a hardened warrior.
Shazah has never witnessed such a scene. Kauzanabi-jo thought this experience dangerous, but the history this one has learned. Shazah's sister may disagree, but the trip was well worth it.
Khali wanted to be there, but Lord Gharesh-ri and Kauzanabi-jo wouldn't have it. How does one expand her horizons if no allows Khali to test her skills?
To be trapped outside these walls while the Veiled Heritance destroys more lives.
It's amazing. I can't believe I witnessed the choosing of the Silvenar!
You've proven yourself a valuable member of the Aldmeri Dominion.
Thank the Eight you returned.
I see Elolir is with you. Keep him safe. He's a decent shot, but he's a fool.
Take those Daedra apart. We'll make sure the barricade stays up.nnAnd take care of Laeneval, will you? She's the last healer we have.
You have accomplished a heroic feat today, but there is more to be done.
I suggest we search for survivors. In these situations most people will try to stay hidden. Perhaps the buildings will yield results.
Back, are you? It's your funeral. nnI knew you couldn't be trusted. Now I get to take it out of your hide.
Caldien .
I'll say a prayer to Y'ffre for my fallen brothers. I hope they'll forgive me for my corwardice. nnThank you once again, traveler.

Mara's grace! I can't tell you how humiliating it is that you had to rescue me yet again. That's the last time. I promise. nnYou need to get the Wards back though, and fast. If my father heard I had one and lost it, he'd put me in the stocks!
They'll come for me soon, and who'll miss me? No one but the rats, I tell you. No one but the rats.nnThey'll come for you too, if you're not careful.
So? Did you convince them? Oh, don't tell me! Talk to Vanus!
You shouldn't be here, traveler.
Is this your land? No? Then leave.
On your way, outsider. You'll never belong here.
Fish aren't for sale. Go catch your own.
The fortress up ahead, they call it the Reaver Citadel. If the Daedra were going for imposing, they damned well succeeded.
My old chum. My bosom companion. My comrade in arms. How long has it been? I've missed you, terribly!nnBy the way, what took you so long? The King is upstairs. He wants to speak to you.
Now comes the true test of your strength and wisdom. Alik'r needs you, <<1>>.nnYou may use the portal behind me to reach the base of the watch.
You return. What have you experienced since last we met?
I'm worried sick about Erinel. I can only pray that whoever hired her kidnappers only wishes to stop the wedding and not worse!
Shall we go and have a proper visit? I'm sure Grunda's prepared something lovely, just for the occasion.
My old life is over. I'll miss Larousse, but these are my people now. I can't just abandon them.
I wish I hadn't run. I'm not a fighter, not like Halalin and Nielas.
You? Who are you?
Still alive. Good.

Hectahame. Lovely isn't it? Especially with its moat of undead and eerily corrupted trees. As much as I know you want to take a peek inside, as long as those wards are up, no one is going anywhere near it.
Has the storm stopped? I don't think I've ever been this sick.
That is all for now. If we have need of you in the future, do not doubt this one will find you.
I'm quite busy at the moment, sorry. I'll be lucky if this haul allows me to keep myself fed, much less pay off my debts. Please leave me to my work.
Did you find out who the Artisan is?
I, Nidras, the Artisan, acknowledge that you rightfully stole my letters, and in exchange for their return, I'll tell you their story.
Hello, hello! This one has tasty foods for the hungry. What can Duzal get you?
Excuse me, sorry. I'm waiting for someone here. Someone who's trying my very last nerve.
Thank you for helping Manthir see how much he loves me. You are the best!

There's more to be done, though. Always is, isn't there?nnPrince Azah's here. He says they've tracked down the third Ansei Ward, and he wants you to join him as soon as possible at the Motalion Necropolis.
I am certain things will return to normal again soon, and these spiders will leave us.nnThey will leave, won't they?
You should've taken the gold.
Yenadar, gone to preach in a High Elf city. Kala is beside herself. Thank you for telling her. This one must arrange passage to the port of Haven at once!
Leave me. I have much to consider.
Apologies, but I must speak to my troops.
Give me a moment to cool down. Talking to those two makes my blood boil.
Don't bring any trouble to <<1>>.
Is there any reason you've chosen to interrupt my thoughts?nnIf so, make it quick. If not, begone.
Valencia wants me to keep playing. So I will. I'll make her proud.
Remove yourself from my presence. You've the stink of this place about you.nnI already can't stand to be here. I don't need  you people clinging to me.
Join the games or join the revelry, sooner or later you'll be back here with a thirst! I just know it. nnWhy not load up now?

The walker is five-clawed after all. Five-clawed, sleek, and fragrant indeed. What will you do, blood-scarred victor? Become drunk and fat?nnThis one hopes not. This one would see you hunt this arena ever more fiercely. It was  an inspiring sight.
This one  feels odd.

So the Veiled Heritance have emerged again in Woodhearth. I see Pelidil and his treachery at the center of this, and once again, you have thwarted his plot. Well done.nnNever mind how this news came to me. My ears now spread throughout Greenshade.
We will never forget how you helped bring peace back to our village.
Please, it wasn't me. How could it be me? I'm a Khajiit. Only Wood Elves can break the Green Pact!
Please take the convicted to judgement, advocate. The wound cannot heal until the burr is removed.
Oh! Hello there. Surprised to see me? So am I, so am I. I do get around, don't I? Haven't the foggiest idea how I do that, quite honestly.
Excellent. Well done. A fantastic experiment, if I do say so myself.
We  we did it. We walked the path and lived. I'm  I'm going to be the Mane. And my sister is dead.
Khalima's life would be unbearable without us.
Get down there and man those ballistae, or that serpent will sink us for sure!
<<1>> has you running all over <<c:2>>. Better you than me.
I heard <<1>> allowed you inside <<c:2>>. Stay on your toes, citizen.
Don't stamp all over the mammoth's tracks! And stand downwind!
Damn troll. Got away again. Impossible to kill. You really got yourself in it this time Ledronor.
The Worm Cultists haven't bothered me in some time. I suppose I have you to thank.nnWait, what happened to <<1>>?

The captain's concerned about <<1>>. She should be! But I spend a lot of time in the crow's nest, so I always try to know what's ahead of me.nnI last saw <<2>> and <<3>> near <<Az:4>>. They may know more about <<5>>'s plans. Neither are mutineers.

So Spinner Eranas was guilty after all. Don't think I'm happy to be proved right. The Spinner's job is to uphold our traditions and pass on our culture to the young. For him to violate the Green Pact  it will take our clan a long time to recover.
The local Altmer still disapprove of our marriage. Quertasse paid someone to steal my censer out of spite. I'm just glad I have Erinel.
I knew it. Gathiel always considered herself above our traditions. A poor match for a Spinner. She deserves what she gets for bringing doom to our village.
Stupid wasp. It keeps getting away from me!
Glaras has been one of Brackenleaf's Briars longer than any of us. She meditates in her tree home, among the trophies of past hunts.

Don't be alarmed if the world around you seems to change. It's a property of the Falinesti Peeper to reveal the true nature of the forest.nnBut be careful, the true nature of the forest can be deadly.
By the Divines, look at these poor souls. I'll bet they were in line to become undead.nnYou and Yahyif go on ahead, find the Master. I'll see if I can get these people some help.
Gedric knows what he's doing. We should press on for Pellingare.
