This is the second time I've lost them.

Oh ho. Now, you have seen how the roles of hunter and hunted are interchangeable. You have stalked your prey and confronted your predator.nnYou are almost ready to become a Briar. One last trial remains.
Things are really moving fast now. Further on and further in. nnI'm ready. A little scared. But ready.

I see the time has come. We must climb this Endless Stair and pray we can stop the Planemeld.nnI hope this ends better than my soul-meld fiasco. I'd hate for either Nirn or Coldharbour to survive only to see the other destroyed. Just like poor Zur.

This is truly an honor for me! I don't know what to say. I hope  <<1>> got to hear the news!nnPlease help protect the village now. I'm no longer allowed to leave <<A:2>> while I learn from the old caretaker.
Their main camp is south of this cavern. They've been pouring in that way! Go!
I hate to be the one to say it, but that poor, lovely creature has to die. It's the only way she'll listen to reason.
How could Nadafa do this to me? And with a monster, no less! Oh, this is such terrible news!
Tharn has requested to speak with you.
The vein in Tharn's forehead looks like it's about to pop. You better see what he wants.
Tharn would like to hiss in your ear. Beware that snake's venom.

Getting all chummy with Titanborn? I enjoy the company of clever, well informed people. You really should try it some time.nnSo, you felled the great Mannimarco. Well played. You've done the Empire a great service.

Fate has dealt us a cruel hand, my brother. I agree with you. Father would not want us to flee our home, but do we dishonor ourselves?nnTo kill him would mean exile, but  I am willing to do this if you command.
It's a pleasure to speak with another knowledge-seeker. Guildmaster Vanus will be pleased!
The Elder Scroll of Chim has returned. This blasphemy must not be allowed again!

Sameer, I beseech you. Let us be gone from this dark place. You must not harm your father's corpse, even in self-defense.nnIf you choose to do this, I cannot stand up for you. You will forfeit your title, and you will be exiled!
I can feel the presence of my ancestors whenever I come here. I am burdened with a great responsibility to honor their sacrifice and uphold their legacy.
Please don't disturb <<1>>. He needs to rest, especially after all that's happened here.
Excellent! I know we'll all be drawing blades together soon enough.nnNow, what can I tell you?

Crestshade was such a quiet town, until that terrible Reezal-Jul arrived.nnPlease, if you haven't already found them, seek out Tharlas and Jonne. Find our personal items. Then maybe we can end this nightmare.
Jone and Jode look down upon us. Bask in that light, that your soul might join them on the path. Zaddo can tell you where you next should go. Where the paths of moonlight lead you.
The moons speak to Saifa. They tell her of your journey.
Traveler. I've got some information here you might find interesting. Someone of your prowess should be able to make a difference.
These shrines are sacred, please show some respect.
If you're looking to join the Briars you should speak with Glaras. Just head up to the top of the tree, you'll find her there.
<<1>> is pacing around again, playing his flute. How can anyone like an instrument that makes such a high pitched sound?
The Elder Scroll of Ni-Mohk must be recovered. It cannot remain in enemy hands!

That <<z:1>> is the only thing of note we've found. There's no end of trouble since we pulled it from the ruin.nnIt's not dangerous, not directly. What I mean to say is that holding it won't rot your hand off. At least, not immediately.
I heard about this place when I was a prisoner in Coldharbour. It's a living nightmare. Be ready for anything.
I heard stories about this foul place during my time in Coldharbour. Chilling. I might have become a permanent resident, were it not for your timely rescue.
The portal will deliver you into the Halls of Torment. Find Sai Sahan and bring him out. He is our last, best hope if we are to locate the Amulet of Kings.
No  please, you can't make me be a monster again!
I was foolish. I tried to convince myself that I was keeping the Pact, that my actions wouldn't catch up with me.nnI'm sorry. At least Gathiel lives.
Don't you understand? I was dying! That plant was my salvation. You would've done the same!

Poor Lleraya. I had hoped to find a way to bring her back from the brink of madness, but it was not meant to be.nnI will not be blinded by sentiment when it comes to Baron Montclair. No. To save Rivenspire, we have only one course left before us.

Glad to see you made it. We were just reviewing our plans and going over what we know about the ruins.nnMy father used to tell me stories about this place. All I can recall is that they always frightened me.
Again, you trouble me at a critical juncture? What must I do to hasten your departure?

My brother and I might be a bit out of our league, but we'll find a way to help.nnWe've explored enough Dwarven ruins and dungeons to fill a hundred lore books. How much different could Molag Bal's Labyrinth be?

I can't imagine what Eranas will do. He spent so much time caring for Gathiel, you know? But, the Green Pact is appeased and we can go back to our lives. Thank you for that.nnIf you're hungry, the meat was untouched! So we could trade, if you like.
I can't believe Gathiel did that. She knew that it would violate the Green Pact. She knew there would be consequences.
The time for words is over. Go, now!
Don't stop now! We'll take care of things here.
No time for words now! Get moving!
The time is at hand. Stop second-guessing yourself, stop questioning your resolve, just stand up and do it. You're ready.
It kills to know Gathiel's gone. And poor Eranas. I can't imagine what he's going throughto nearly lose her to that illness, and then this happens.
So Gathiel's gone, I see. I see .nnYou know what this means, don't you? The torchbugs. They're listening to us through the torchbugs.
Huh. Well, I guess she was sick anyway. One of those situations where the forest reclaims its own, I suppose.
<A quiet stillness hangs over the shrine, but you feel a sense of anticipation.>
You won't escape! You'll die in here, like the others!
Didn't Adusa tell you not to do anything stupid? Why does this one even bother giving advice?
Well, what are you waiting for? Find a tear and let's get on with this.
So? Where are the other survivors? Adusa doesn't see them, so that means you need to get back to the looking, yes?
You should leave before the curse gets you too.
I feel horrible. My mouth tastes like ash and dirt.
Ugh, kill me. Just end it all.
I've never felt this bad. Never.
i feel horrible
i feel horrible
i feel horrible
i feel horrible
i feel horrible
We will meet with Kasura as soon as I am well enough to travel.
May Arkay bless you, <<1>>.

Z'en's price! I knew if I banged on this door long enough someone would come.nnNever dreamed it'd be another Tree-Sapper, though. I'd ask how you ended up here, but I got more pressing matters. Can you spring me before the trolls come back?
I'm not sure how we managed to survive. It was so horrible. But since we're still alive, maybe there's some hope left in Moira after all. Maybe there are others out there.
You came back? All right, let's try that again.
This great time of unrest within the Guild is at an end. You've done very well, comrade.
I hear things, deep inside my mind. Voices. Sounds. I don't want to listen! Make it stop!
Don't worry, I'll be fine. Make them regret the day they stepped onto Dominion soil.
Are you sure this place is safe? And who's the strange Khajiit lady? Oh, I feel faint!
Janeve  my sister . Reezal-Jul afflicted her with his blood-curse. She's becoming a  a vampire.nnVampires are evil. Totally, utterly evil. But by Arkay, this is my sister!
Turn back, citizen. <<1>> is  I don't know what to call it, exactly.

I don't remember how I came to be here in this cell. When I woke you were just standing there, foaming at the mouth.nnCount yourself lucky that <<1>> had no desire to treat you like a puppet. Unlike myself.
I can never decide between Choice and Free Will. Which will triumph in the end? But why not settle the matter for me?nnOr you could yank a lever, but that's hardly fun for either of us.
I'm sorry I missed being able to shove my blade deep into <<1>>. I was kind of looking forward to that.nnI'll make sure Captain Janeve gets the same training I received. It's the least I can do.
Rest easy, Vestige. We've come a long way, but there is more yet before us. Molag Bal must be thwarted. The Planemeld must be stopped.
Honor and faith to you, my friend. Kasura sends her regards. She is recovering quickly, and reconstruction on the Abbey of Blades has already begun.
I'm right behind you. Let's go get that amulet!
Place the stone on <<1>>'s forehead. Every second that beast is free is one she might use to escape!
The Empire collapses and the Gray Vipers flourish. The first is beyond our ability to fix, but we can do much about the second.
You have accepted a contract. The guild expects you to fulfill it.
Personally, I like to crush bandits' skulls with a warhammer. However you do it, kill as many of them as you can.
You are angry. It is to be expected.
Well, that was a deeply unpleasant experience.
Now that I'm safe, I'd prefer to keep it that way. If it isn't too much trouble, could we please hurry up and get out of here?
It's good to see you again. And I do see you, in my own way. You are a wound in time, a tear in reality that shouldn't exist and cannot long endure.
We're going to try to put this behind us. To start over. But we'll never forget the friends and family we lost. Never.
Sometimes it feels like these cultists really are worms. When you slice them to pieces, you just wind up with more of them!
Mannimarco is aware of our presence. We need to find the ring and leave this place.
He promised me again and again. And, fool that I am, I believed himagain and again.nnI will never meet another like him. Perhaps it is better that way.
Welcome back, my friend.
I'm pleased that you are still willing to work with me, Vestige. I hope to make amends for my part in all this.
You tear away the Architect's legion like weeds.nnThe Harvester that possesses my soul waits just across this bridge.
Tread carefully, friend. You walk through dangerous territory.
I think I heard something! If those monsters return, I'll give them what for!
Please, leave me some room to treat the injured here.nnNot to be rude - bad circumstances for a chat, that's all.

A Bretonwhat was I thinking? I should've known a pretty little Breton lady wasn't interested in me!nnIt was just that we had so much in common. She was quiet, she wanted to be a mage  but it was all a lie! Now I'll be kicked out of the Guild!
I wish I could join you, but  with all those frost trolls, I'd only hold you back.nnYou be careful in that cave, would you?
So the Emerald Chalice turns ordinary people into green Goblins? Remarkable!

Rashan will show you how you can be of assistance.nnDo not be mistaken though, outsider. If you take any action to harm what little nature remains uncorrupted here, she will go straight for your throat.

Who would have guessed it would be an outsider who would show up and kill Uela?nnI doubt this means we'll start inviting families from Evermore out to visit, but maybe, just maybe, we can be a little more friendly.
You travel with <<1>>? He has proven himself a friend to the Falinesti Faithful.nnThere are questions written upon your faces. What is it you seek?

Pox on it! I would've given my axe to have been there when you gave that head to Captain Hjurrun! nnI heard his jaw just about hit the ground. You've given me a good laugh, friend, and a little bit of hope too.

Ah, the queen's champion! Honor to meet you. Means we're that much closer to getting paid. That's good, because I didn't come to Evermore for the women.nnAre you ready then? As long as you're good with the plan, this thing's going to be a breeze.

Hi there. Queen Arzhela told me about all you did for the city. Sounds like they should be building a statue.nnAnyways, compared to what you've already dealt with, this should be a cinch. Really, our part only comes into play if there's a problem.
He took the Walking City? He took my home?nnOr is this another of his lies?
The crypt is to the east, at the top of the stair. Come.
What? Follow me. We'll talk when we reach the  gah  safe spot.
All that's left is to face the Architect. He's defended and he's powerful, but if he can be defeated .nnYou've made miracles happen today, my friend.
Speak to Rashan.

I must admit, I'm not comfortable with this little jaunt. Sancre Tor is in the mountains of Colovia, and Colovians are the worst kind of Imperialsbackwards mountain men without any sense of decorum. At least Varen will feel right at home.
This is absurd!
I barely made it out of there alive. Those things. They're like nothing I've ever seen.
Another one? Curious. What do you want?
I did what needed to be done. Isabeth knew this. Let's hope her father can open his eyes.
This is Denille's last hope. If this fails, the worst is inevitable.
For the love of Mara, I didn't think I'd see the end of this day. Did Captain Gaercroft, my father, send you?
We couldn't stop those monsters. I fear that soon all of Rivenspire may be lost!
So this trip turned out to be far shorter and far more fortuitous than I expected.nnThat's assuming you're up to the challenge, of course.
I guess it's a good thing we gave the bows to Baandari after all.
I deserve to suffer. All those lives ruined because of my petty need for vengeance. I deserve worse. Leave me be.
You convinced Knight Commander Cheryline to give up the bows? If I had asked her, she wouldn't even have spared me a wooden dagger. nnShe must really like you!
You saw the thief, yes? Or smelled him, perhaps? He was quite filthy. This one will be scrubbing the stench of him out of his clothes for a week, at least!
I'm sorry we can't chat for long. I'm waiting for someone.
The information you have obtained for us is invaluable.nnGo. Do what you must. And be certain that we will do the same.
The Fevered Mews  I haven't thought about that place since I was a child.
Quite the haul for your first day. You don't do anything half way, do you?
Well, all's well that end's well, right? Except for the real mysterywho in Northpoint was pulling Leonce's strings? And why?nnI don't think I'll sleep well until that gets resolved.

Speak of Sheogorath! You've caused quite a stir! Merchants speak of a black wind robbing them blind! Your open hand is blessed on every street corner!nnIf you were looking to make an impression, you have!
I remember now. The translationwe misinterpreted it. We assumed the Crag housed a powerful healing artifact. But we were wrong.nnThe hillside community, though. Why didn't I ever look into that?

When you went below into the crypts this foul icy fog rolled in. The earth shook and those Dolmen emerged from the ground beneath our feet. nnWe retreated here to await your return, the rest you can clearly see.
Hungry  so hungry. A sweetcake would be nice. Candied mammoth tail swimming in sparkle-syrup. Honeyfly bisque over a comb the size of my head  oh, I can almost taste it!
You look like someone who cares about the health of a community. We need more people like you in these troubled times.
Smells good. Maybe, if I wait, they share.
Back of the line, bug nose! I was here first!

There was a time this place was nothin' but a game trail, if you believe it. Blacksaps used to ambush old coins not familiar with the Valenwood.nnThat's where I came in. Know these woods like the back of my hand. Blacksaps never saw us comin'.
If we can't get the information we need, we may be better off barricading Evermore completely and preparing for siege.nnIf you can help, please speak with Captain Gaercroft. We need it.
He sleeps now, thank S'rendarr.

You're such a good person! I know that Puddles will be home in no time now that you're out there looking for her.nnI could see it in her eyes when we arrived. Puddles really wanted to go out and explore this new city. She's very curious, you know.
This place, it speaks to me. It whispers in my ear, sings into my soul. It runs through my blood like cold fire. nnBut none of that matters. When we save Leila, it will all be worth it.
Don't mind Wylon. He's just angry that the shard's effects faded away. He knows you didn't mean for this to happen to me, Verandis.
Looks like you've made your introductions. Time to get to work.
We should honor who the prince was in his life, not the abomination he became in death.nnI will leave you to your mourning.
I'm glad you saw through Gasteau's lies.
Ah! If it isn't the five-clawed walker who saved our herbalists! Crazy Eye is very impressed!nnAre you here to help me fight these dungy Imperial dogs?
Hello, bloodkith! Heard you gutted some bandits in the attack.

You're going to the crypt, aren't you? If those churlish rats have raised Eamond, you strike him down. Don't hesitate. nnI loved my husband, but I'd rather see him burned than in that  state. Whatever happens, just make sure I don't see him.
We have enough trouble around here without the noble houses bickering among themselves.
This is no time for idle talk. We need to destroy the Fangs of Chaos to weaken the Dark Anchor!
Greetings, guild-sister. How may I help you?
Ah, my friend! Your return, it is well timed.nnFor some reason, Montclair's forces have attacked the castle. This one can't imagine why they would do such a thing.
Careful! For a moment there, I thought you were the Cloak, coming for Captain Marck. Guess I get kind of jittery in the field.
Say the word and I'll open a portal to <<1>>. Once you pass through, it will seal behind you.nnIf you have anything to do before you leave, now is the time.
About time you got here. I was afraid I was going to have to do this job on my own.
About time you got here. I was afraid I was going to have to do this job on my own.
About time you got here. I was afraid I was going to have to do this job on my own.
I do not understand why this inn is so popular with travelers. The beds are like rocks and the mead tastes like the sweat of a dog.nnI will not spend one night more here than is absolutely necessary.

Gold. Some people believe we're too obsessed with it, that it controls everything. But I think that's actually a good thing. nnHow else do we create a standard for the value of social and cultural exchange? Gold is the best way. It really is.
<<1>> and his sons rose against the rightful king of the Valenwood. This prison may not be the perfect solution, but it suits them better than a quick death.
<<<1>> wags his tail happily.>
Dark days are upon us, friend. Arkay's foes spread like wildfire. Only his holy relics can save us now.
Hail, traveler! Welcome to EvermoreBangkorai's jewel of joy and plenty!
I'm surprised you made it. The Houses informed me of what took place in the Doomcrag. Most soldiers would have perished inside of there.nnYet here you stand. Commendable and respectable.
Have you found the crown?
I've said all I'm going to say. We both know this isn't true justice. If your Dominion means what it says, it will give my family a public trial.
My patience wears thin. If this crisis has taught us anything, it's that a nation needs a single ruler. I just hope the High King sees that as well.
The time has come to crown a ruler of Rivenspire. The Light shines on us all, but a nation needs a single leader to look up to.
Tough family, huh? Not sure it was his fault, exactly, but I've been known to do some crazy things for a woman.nnNever anything like this, though. I do have limits, you know.
Lyris has more to tell you, Vestige. Speak with her.
I've dealt with these Worm Cultists before. They use the darkest magic, and they don't fight fair. Be careful.
Good to see you again, my friend. Kazirra asked me to send her regards. Actually, she said something about the moons. You know how it goes.
What is the matter? You left before we could finish!
I'm sorry you had to witness that. I knew <<1>>'s citizens were zealous about the Green Pact, but sometimes they go hunting for trouble.
If you're looking to buy something, go inside and speak to Sabir. I'm sure he has what you need.
<<<1>> wags his tail happily.>
You're the last person I'd expected to see in this backwood. Or, at the least, it would be a wood if there were more trees.
All those lives, ruined by me. I deserve to suffer.
I deserve to suffer. All those lives ruined because of my petty need for vengeance. I deserve worse. Leave me be.
Hallowed. It is good to finally put a face to all the tales I've heard.
Take care inside, Hallowed. This one remembers his cleansing. Many things from the past came to the fore, many old wounds re-opened. Stay close to the Champions, and keep them safe.
May Arkay's light guide you on your journey.
Hurry up and move into position. I'm getting antsy for some vampire slaying.
What are you doing? Go activate the blood fountain already.
I don't guess you've seen my friend, Garth, around, have you? Middling height, anxious-looking fellow, with a bit of a beer gut?
You've returned. What have you learned of the Khajiit Embassy?

I heard what you said to the king. <<1>>, a traitor; my wife's killer, a loyal servant; and I, <<2>>'s representative in <<3>>, required to thank you for your efforts.nnVery well. I'll provide no reason to question my duty to the Dominion.
My friend <<1>> has gone missing, and I'm worried he got himself into trouble inside the cave to the north.
Good luck in your battle. We will be with you in thought and spirit.
So, you're to kill Brinarch? Good. Tamriel will be better for it.
We're very close now, thanks to you.
My hunter. The scent of your success surrounds you.
Daedra take it! Gargoyle spit, and on my best breeches. Now let's see .nnReally, this is quite revolting.
Well, friend, I'm glad to see you were able to help out with the High King's arrival. It's nice to see that some people are willing to do their part for crown and country.
You're confident, I'll give you that. Strode right up to the king.
Meet us in Vulkhel Guard. We'll head there right away.nnAs soon as we finish our drinks.

I've received word that Northpoint has been liberated and we march now to face Montclair himself in the Doomcrag.nnI know that between you and Verandis we can stop the baron's evil plan before it spreads any further. Gods be with you, my friend.

Every night since the massacre, I've dreamt of the horrors the Jade Butcher brought to <<1>>. It seems fitting to meet the one who brought her to justice on the very spot she slew the Blacksap.nnI wonder, will I have nightmares of you?
Our farm  everything we owned. It's all gone.
All this time on the road  it's been hard. Makes me wish I had better boots, you know?
Verandis told us stories of this place. How the current trouble began here. Shornhelmall of Rivenspirethreatened because of a single event that occurred in the Doomcrag.
Thanks again. Now I can give the treethane his bow back. I'm a free Elf!nnTake care of yourself out there. <<1>> is a dangerous place, as <<2>> discovered.
Damn it. What went wrong? The vampire lord should have appeared by now. nnWhere are Zungarg and Agalir?
What happened to our family is terrible, but as the bards say, life goes on.nnMy sister and I came up here to  well, to give them a proper burial.
Why? Why did they have to leave us?
I think that Countess Tamrith and Baron Dorell both could be excellent rulers. The important thing is that we crown someone. And today must be the day.
Fear not, Vestige. When Sai Sahan and the others return, we will slip into the shadow of Sancre Tor and retrieve the Amulet of Kings.
Are you with the Vinedusk Rangers? The Justiciars? The Fighters Guild?nnIt doesn't matter. I know why you're here.
<<1>> says you're to thank for uncovering a traitor in our midst.
I don't understand . How can I cook dinner now?
My brother  my Nedras. All this gold .
I'll be better off without him. Yes. Now that I know he's not coming back, I can move on with my life. Better off without that stupid mule!
Yenadar, gone to preach in a High Elf city. Kala is beside herself. Thank you for telling her, traveler. This one must arrange passage to the port of Haven at once!
Please do not strike me. I am not with the Bitterhand. I am as a tree buried beneath the ground, stuck in darkness and doomed to die.nnI am not even a bandit  any more.

Well, kiss a troll and call me pumpkin! I know you! From Shornhelm! Did Baron Dorell send you?nnI was the Orc. In the cage. Not my most shining moment, but it's not like I'm a noble or anything. No matter. I'm just glad you're here.
Fortunately, I'm on the stealthy side. That's not Snaruga's way, though.nnThe old girl gave the Imperials too many black eyes. They dare not trust her with a pick!
No one seems to be asking where these Imperials are coming from. We're a long way from Cyrodiil. Something is amiss here.
Don't drag your feet. The slow hunter never catches his prey, and I can't keep this gateway open forever.
These Imperial dogs are vicious but smart. They know they can't beat us in a direct confrontation, so they starve us out. I'd like to compliment their commander before killing him.
It's good that you're here, my friend, though I'm afraid I may be dying .
Imagine! The chance to see <<c:1>> operate.nnConservator <<2>> is preparing <<3>> as we speak.
<<1>> knew the dangers. What hubris, to do such a thing.
I've ruined everything .
Good luck .
Have you seen my husband, Najan? We should go to him.
Touch the symbol of Arkay. Profane the Forsaker.
Nothing to see here. Move along.
Heroes, gods, Imperials  who's in charge here? You. You've earned the blessings of the heroes, but blessings will only get you through the door.nnAre you really ready for what lies on the other side?
This is rather disconcerting. I don't believe I've ever had a conversation with a monkey before.
I must seek my fortune. And you must go elsewhere to seek yours.
You know, there were rumors that Ranser was betrayed by his chief military advisor, General Dathieu.nnIf Ranser was decapitated, that might suggest the rumors were true. How can we be sure, though?
Your kin live among the mortals. They may be wearing rags or crowns. They may hide within or rise above the masses.nnAs your Bloodspeaker found you, you must find them. They await.
Go on. Go find the rest of our assault team. I'll have this place all cozy like in no time!

The falls you seek are southwest of here, overlooking Gil-Var-Delle. Simply let some of the water from the vial fall at each crest, and the flow will carry it across Gil-Var-Delle so that the earth may drink and be cleansed.
Even with a single performer back on the job, I see smiling faces. I think we're starting to draw a crowd!nnWhatever you've been doing, keep doing it!
May Arkay drive back the darkness, forever more.
Oh! You took the shipment to <<1>>? And you don't smell like fungus and rotten meat  good work.
Any luck with the supplies? They should still be in <<1>>.
My you smell lovely  delightful. How delightful.
As soon as he gets home, I'm going to give my husband a piece of my mind. Edouard will be lucky if I don't throw him out after all this trouble.
I apologive profusely for the burden that escorting <<1>> surely inflicted upon you.nnI will safeguard him from here, so that he takes nothing of this place with him aside from stories.
I owe Ufa a favor, not you. Be on your way to do what you must. I'm sure I'll see you later at The Drowsy Owl Inn.
You saved her. Thank you. I don't know what I'd  nevermind.

Ah yes, I recall you from before. You failed to find the relic I was hunting in the Alik'r. At least you didn't fail to find <<1>>.nnI don't suppose you'd be willing to help me find something else, just to prove you're not entirely inept?
An abandoned house. Lovely. One day, my dear, you'll need to take me somewhere nice.nnWell, let's go investigate.
That's an interesting story. If Naruk had Kaleen under duress, wouldn't she alert the guard? Now I'm curious.
Thank you. A find like this is incredibly rare. It could greatly advance our understanding of the Valenwood Ayleids and their unique dialect. I must begin translating immediately!
No. Don't tell me he's dead. He can't be.
Is that your friend? See to her. I'll watch your back.
I think I'm ready to swing a sword again.
Please. I need your help.

Can you believe this? The fool's turned himself into iron!nnIt's like a practical joke. I keep expecting my boss to step out from behind a rock and tell me he just wanted to see how I'd react. I'd carry the bastard if he wasn't so damn heavy.
Good meeting, walker! Do you have a moment? My business partner is in trouble and this one could use some aid.
Fascinating! And a bit intimidating.nnBut I suppose you could say that about much of Ayleid construction.
This is wonderful. After all these years  it's going to work, I know it.
<The Bounty board has a place for me to post my report.>
<The Bounty board has a place for me to post my report.>
<The Bounty board has a place for me to post my report.>
It is no small feat to take on an Imperial cohort. Mauloch must approve.
Wait! Please, stay your blade and listen.
Hello there. I suggest you don't try to pick me up. You'll only injure your back.nnDon't ask for any long-winded explanations either. It's tiring to talk when you're made of iron.
The tension between the locals and the Imperials makes it difficult to concentrate.
Hold it. You're not working for the Imperials are you?
<<1>> believes we Covenant troops require a symbol to rally behind, but he is mistaken. nnThe Old Tower is occupied by an Imperial Cohort. No stolen hat will change those odds.
I do not know if <<1>> will last much longer. nnBring him this thing he yearns for, that he may feel victory in his hands once more before embracing a warrior's death.

Halt there. Bangkorai Garrison is on lockdown since the death of King Eamond. Only Knights of Saint Pelin and members of the royal family are allowed in.nnAlso, if you were planning on going to Evermore, you might want to reconsider that.

It sounds archaic, but the Blacklight Raiders were well-roundedwarrior, cleric, thief, and mage.nnThe mage wrote a letter to one of the others telling how to open the lockbox. Between the letter and the gravestones, I hope we can solve it.
Any luck?
The soldiers said I could fish for a while longer. You can ask them, they'll tell you I'm allowed here.
A soldier already told me to return to <<Ac:1>>. But let me fish a little longer, all right? I'll head back shortly.
All done, warrior?
Well met, friend. I've heard a lot about you!
This is hopeless! Baron Montclair forces me to mix concoctions that I know won't do any good.nnIf he'd just listen to me,  I could show him exactly how to heal his wife and end her suffering.
Well scamp, you don't look any worse for wear. Maybe you should put the ale down every once in a while and pick up a sword. Hah!
How are you doing, milksop? Kill any big scary monsters this week?
They say it may take weeks for the performers to start their shows back up, but I am worried if I leave I'll miss it.
Even with a single performer back on the job, I see smiling faces. I think we're starting to draw a crowd!nnWhatever you've been doing, keep doing it!
Off you go, then. Ta!
Ah, our magnanimous prince. Such a kind and noble ruler, don't you agree?

Fine, I stand corrected. You weren't just trying to trick me.nnYou've got my thanks, for whatever that's worth. Now that <<1>> is dead, the rest of us should be able to hold out until reinforcements arrive.
Your drunken exploits gave the bards much to work with. I think your battle with the giant will make a fine song. Still, I am sorry for this inconvenience.
Hurry, friend! Who knows what that mad Argonian is planning to do to poor Janeve.
Have you talked to Bumnog yet? He's got something important to tell you. About, you know, things.
Sai used to quote his book at me. "The sword is the self. Its edge is the mind."nnI never understood what he meant, but now I think I do. Being out and about keeps me sharp.
My friend. I have wondered how you have fared. Tell me, how can this old blade help you?
Get after them. Make sure the harpies don't kill them before they've washed that stench off!
We will escort these men to our border. They are not as skilled as we were led to believe, and I'll be sure to let this be known.
Before you go in, I need to talk to you.
Can you talk to Bumnog? He's got something he really, really needs to say to you.
Ah. I almost feel sorry for him. Almost.
You better hurry. We need to get those hostages free as fast as possible.nnMeet me back in the center of town after you've taken care of things.

Welcome to Fell's Run. Normally we'd welcome you with open arms and throw a feast, but not this year.nnWe had a terrible harvest, and times are hard. Might be better if you moved on and spent the night in Northpoint. Come back next year.
What in Oblivion do you want? nnUnless you can haul it yourself, don't tell me you have a load of grain that needs to be ground at the mill. The constable's deputy just confiscated my damn wagon.
So we're going to live? I thought those bandits were going to kill us!

So here we are. The moment of truth. I can now look upon the face of the one who will be my judge. nnI hope you understand that I am in no way trying to deny my past wrongdoings, nor would I argue that those acts should be forgiven.

Oh, well. It was worth a try. I knew she was something of a long shot, with an attitude like that.nnI'd probably have been forced to beat her down every other day just to keep her in line. Maybe it's better that she won't enlist.
You have done well, my friend. You have a singular knack for shredding Lleraya's illusions.nnCome. Let's find out if the way ahead is truly clear.
Talk to Skordo. He has a plan. It's a bit crude, but it just might work.nnAt least, it has the advantage of being remarkably simple and easy to remember. I appreciate that in a plan.
I see plenty of Montclair's monsters, but no survivors. Let's keep looking.
It has been a grueling day. Restock and rest. We'll begin the march to the Doomcrag when you're ready.
Some of my soldiers seem to be having second thoughts about our grand purpose. About the faith that guides us through the darkness.nnI really don't have time for such distractions right now!
We need to find the others before it's too late. Lead the way upstairs, but stay alert.
We are lucky you came along when you did. Had you been but a moment later  I hate to think what might have happened.
It's so strange to have Federic return after all this time only to leave again. But I think I'm done being lonely. <<1>> has been wonderful to me. It's time I gave her a chance.
And everything goes back to the way it was  I don't know how I feel about that.
My wife, is she ?
Whatever will become of our dearest Arlie, now? With <<1>> and Federic leaving, it's as though the light has gone out of her eyes.nnPerhaps I can find someone in <<2>> to keep her company.
I've decided to make this a personal challenge. I'm going to turn things around for the Shornhelm Guard. They'll be the most feared outfit in all the Covenant by next year. You can bet on it!
Thank you for walking with me Adept. I know what I need to do, now. I just need a few more minutes outside before I return to complete the work on the volume you found.
Kynareth's blessing be upon you.nnHave you come to put yourself to the challenge, and ride in the race?
My daughter may not be happy, but she learned a valuable lesson.
You can't have your ballom pudding and eat it, too. I hope our new ruler realizes that. Gods know, I do.
What happened? Where's Verandis?
I didn't have time to explore when we were here last. It's far larger than I realized.nnWho knows what treasures may rest within these ruins? The Ayleids have always been such a mystery.
Speak quickly. I am very busy and our Order is stretched to the breaking point.
I can use the root words embedded in the text to make rough translations.
Good day to be out on the sea, isn't it? So why am I standing around here on the docks you might ask ? That's good damn question. nnAsk Captain Marck.

It's good to see you here. It's long overdue for Rivenspire to get a new ruler! nnAs you can see, Julien and Shuga are here. They've surprised even me with their valor in battle. Sadly, we lost Martin. He went down fighting, though. That's something.
The burnt bones foretold death, and death came. They also showed me things which confused me. Hidden things, secret things. And the arrival of someone who can help.nnWhat news do you bring?
Excuse me. Hara says you've joined our number.nnThat's very exciting, because I believe I've discovered something that can help us understand who or what the Celestials really are.
Why don't they simply put Baron Dorell in charge and be done with it. He's obviously the one who should be running things around here.
Ever since Countess Tamrith returned to the city, I've felt much better about our chances. She's her father's daughter, that's for sure!
It seems our troubles never end. First, the mad king sends us to war against Wayrest. And now the nobles who are supposed to protect us are fighting against each other.nnWill it never end?
Are we safe here in the lower city? Will Baron Montclair's forces attack us down here? I can't stand all this waiting!
A friendly face! Good, good. This day may not be a complete failure.
Ah! Oh! Oh  you're  not who I thought you were.nnI'd clear out, stranger. Spiders in this cave. Lots and lots of spiders!
Stars above, finally someone with a bit of sense to them. Please, traveler. Help out a fair trader, aye?
These Covenant soldiers are prickly sons of bitches. But we'll hold them back.nnI'm sure of it.
I remember when I'd hunt here for days and not see a soul. The war was on, and people stayed behind walls or stuck to roads. Those days are behind us.
Shoes? Shoes are for lesser men! My manly toes need to breathe! It's a medicinal fact.
Use the torch to burn the dead. I'll follow behind you and perform the ritual of sanctification.
Priest Marnest is surprisingly more helpful than I anticipated. Comforting the refugees, performing blessings and rituals, cooking and cleaning. He even tells a pretty good story.
Ah, it's good to see you again, friend. And what can I do for the hero of Northpoint?
You have the gratitude of Sen Dres, my new friend. I'd raise a goblet of wine with you, if there was time. But there isn't.

You have come deep into Valenwood. There is nothing for you here. One such as you is needed to the north, though.nnThe Wood Orcs encroach on the forest. They trample the grass. They chop down trees. They must be stopped.
Good luck, traveler. May you succeed in your service to Her Majesty.
Hey there, traveler. Go well on your journey.
I'm going to stay here with my brother. See what you can find in the chambers we passed through.
Keep your distance. No need to contract the plague on my account.
I can't find them anywhere!
It's horrible they're capturing people all over the city!
They're all dead. I'm sure of it. Now how can I possibly complete our mission?
The Llodos plague  I have no idea why, but it's clear to me that the Maulborn curative is actually the source of the disease.nnWhatever they're planning, you have to stop them.
It's horrible there are injured people all over the city!
Were you able to acquire any samples of the Maulborn curative? I'm really curious to see what the elixir is made of.
Thank the Eight! Please, you have to help us. We can't keep them contained much longer!

I must emphasize to both you and these Bosmer that we did not desire this duty, nor do we take any joy in it, but we cannot act against our directives.nnThe only way one might circumvent this is to destroy us, and that would be very difficult to do.
Auri-El preserve me! A friendly face! Please, you have to help us. We can't keep them contained much longer!
Always good to speak with another knowledge-seeker. Guildmaster Vanus will be pleased!
I knew you'd find everything Nilyne needed! Please, talk to the alchemist and give her the additives she's been waiting for.
Erunor will make an excellent caretaker. He's always been a stickler for details. I remember when he was just a lad, before the village left last time.nnOr maybe that was his older brother? Hmm.
Haven't you ever made a potion before? My notes are by the table. I need to care for my patient now, but my notes should be able to guide you through the process.
Once again, you show up just when you're needed most. Nilyne has been waiting patiently for you. Well, mostly patiently.nnPlease, talk to her and let her know what you were able to find.
I'd welcome you to the Brooding Elf Inn, but I'm not in a very friendly mood. Between the plague and the Maulborn, I'm at my wit's end.nnStill, if there's something I can get you, feel free to ask.
Good, good. I know we'll be drawing blades together soon enough.nnNow, what can I tell you?

It's good to have another new face around here. I'm just a student that came to study with the Star-Gazers. I never expected I'd see an event like this! It's terrifying, but it could mean a chance to learn so much more about the Celestials.
Good luck exploring the caves of Daen Seeth. The Ashlands is an exciting place for travelers and adventurers. nnMe? I'll just stay here in my nice, cozy tavern. Mmm  Bile Beer.
It's good to know there are travelers such as yourself out there. Keeping the Ashlands safe from  subhumanoids. Hmph.

You are generous to humor two silly old men, but those seeds would mean so much to us. When we were young, we used to sneak away from the clan and come here to be together.nnLying here among the Nereid's Smile, it seemed like we had forever.
The library is grand, isn't it? Not as grand as it once was, I suppose. But the years are long and the past has no greater enemy than the present moment.
I am the answer to all questions and the question behind every answer.nnNo need to introduce yourself. Your name is already recorded in my realm of Apocrypha.
If you ever need assistance, you need only to ask.nnI owe you the largest of favors. As do my people.
Those are some formidable wounds. I haven't seen lacerations like that since Fungal Grotto!nnAt least you're alive. Get back in there, already.
Now that we're inside the temple, there's something I must tell you.nnThe Seeker's Archive holds vast reserves of secret knowledge, but I didn't tell you the reason for this.
Hello hello! This one has tasty foods for the hungry and delicious drinks for the thirsty. What can I get you?

Shor's bones, I can't thank you enough. In time, the body you and Valaste have formed for me will fade. But with this charm, you'll never forget our trials together. I take comfort in that.nnAre you ready?
Tu'whacca smiles upon you this day wayfarer, for you are not caught in the calamity at the main docks.nnBy any chance do you have experience dealing with the dead?
Can you believe it? These people  our people who drank the water  they're starting to return. They seem to be in their right minds again!

Before we can stop Yamanu-ko, you need to bring down the wards protecting the Apex Tower.nnYamanu-ko's apprentices set the wards in the other mage towers. Disable those wards, and I'll meet you at the Apex Tower.
We came so close to freedom!
Be warned, the concentrated energy in the shards has caused unpredictable elemental storms. nnYou'd be wise to avoid them while you harvest the elemental infusions.

All these years. He kept the body. It's been so long, and the torture of my soul so recent  I had forgotten.nnIt was a single stab through the chest with a blade so sharp it pierced my ward. Possibly with the Daedric blade he now wields.

Oh, good. You're here. I'm worried about Hara. She's clearly tired, but she refuses to rest. She's going to make herself ill!nnSpeaking of which, she wants to see you as soon as you can manage. It sounded urgent.
I sense a village in the distance.
According to everything I've read, breaking that Sigil Stone up ahead will bring us, and everyone who came through that Gate, back to Whisper Grove.
Hara hasn't been herself lately. It has me ill at ease.nnI know Nazdura was concerned about Hara's well-being. Maybe she can help make sense of this.
You've returned!
We have much to discuss with Hara of the Star-Gazers. Make haste and find our other selves. We will meet you at the winery when you have completed the task.
Find the other aspects quickly.nnIf the Serpent catches their scent, he will stop at nothing to claim them.
You found it! Well, that's one down.
I can't believe you're still looking through her things.
I don't think you should be doing this.
Keep looking around here. I'm sure we'll turn up something.
What can Azbael help you with?
Glad you made it.
I can't believe he would stoop so low. I'll never beat him now.

Your will to survive is impressive. With the Sculptor gone and none to command the prison's flesh constructs, the Warden's sword is broken.nnThere are wretched mortals in cells up ahead. Free them if you must, but you face the Gravelight Sentry next.
Looking for some outrageous bargains on weapons and armor? I'm afraid I'm out of stock at the momentnnYou look like an able sort. Perhaps you'd be willing to help me collect my wares?
Just take the iron ore to the Blacksmithing Station and extract the raw materials from it to make an ingot.

Be careful if you're going upstairs. These mages are running experiments, and I met several of them a couple floors up who didn't take kindly to visitors.nnIf I had more allies I'd have given them Mauloch's fury. If only Brulo would get here.
Go ahead. Don't be shy.

"Step 3: Choose A Stylenn"Every race has a style of blacksmithing, and each favors a specific material. I call this a 'style material' because it's easy to remember. When you have a style material and some iron ingots, you're ready to make a weapon."
What are you waiting for, a kiss on the cheek? Get out there and kill that cat! Hah!
On Quest Step Talk to Gwenneth
Done with Quest 7
It's about time you showed up, rook. We were going to steal this ship without you.

You were at the observatory earlier, weren't you? I thought I saw you talking to Hara.nnAre you going to visit the tavern? If so, watch out for two lunatic High Elves. I don't know if they're dangerous, but you can never tell.

I suppose we're allowing just anybody to enter the Archive now. The Learned One brought many gifts with her when she entered, but she undid our seal on the Archive, and I'm beginning to wonder about the drawbacks.nnDo try to avoid the upper floors.
Everything's in place, now. We can see about breaking our last member out of prison.
You're safe! Do you have everything?

You are very welcome among our order, my new friend. It's a frightening time and we could use allies like you. Feel free to get to know the other Star-Gazers here. I'm sure some of them could use your help.
All right, we made it in, but we've got a new challenge. I don't know what to expect from the captain of this prison, but she can't be a good person. Keep your guard up.
They want us to speak with the captain? I don't think this is a good sign. Be wary, regardless.
Shinsun-ra? Great. I was hoping we could avoid encountering her, but guess that was wishful thinking. She's a nasty, petty dictator, and we're in her kingdom. Be wary.
I'll pack things up here and meet you by the boat. See if you can't find out what happened here.nnI don't like seeing my work this badly mangled.
Let me know when you are ready, and the race will begin.
Aye?
Like a Ra Gada cavalryman. Like the very vision of a Ra Gada cavalryman!nnTalaya will be mad that you bested her course, but no matter. Splendid riding!
You made it look easy, didn't you? nnI suspect Queen Ayrenn will find it difficult to best your time, but hopefully, she will at least be open to the challenge.
Hm. It seems you did not complete the course. That's no reason to give up, however! Would you like to try again?
You have this day one to remember, wayfarer! You've proven the course is a good one. nnNow, I just have to convince this Rigurd the Brash to unclude the challenge as part of the Konunleikar.

You have the makings of an amazing rider. I suspect no female hoavoar ever ran the trail in such good time.nnAnd even if they did, of course, the male hoarvoars soon had their way with them. So be grateful that you are not a female hoarvoar.
That was an impressive ride. If you had been leading the Imperials when they sought to subdue Valenwood . who knows? nnThings might have ended much differently.
Good ride, my friend. I suspect there are some Wood Orcs out there who will wake up tonight in terror, hearing your thundering hoofbeats in their fear-ridden dreams.
Your skill at riding is truly unmatched, wayfarer. I had doubted if even you could complete this course, but you have proven me wrong.
Well now. I suspect Talaya was more than a little bit frustrated to see you finish the course so easily.nnThis is good, though. Like you, she seems to thrive when facing a challenge.

In my youth I heard tales of a mad Reachman who would ride the steppes. No one moved over the rugged mountains with more speed than he.nnI say your performance today has given me a glimpse of his prowess!
I have heard harrowing stories of plague and Daedric mischief across Deshaan. I hope that you were not too heavily impeded in your challenge.
I heard tales of horsemen in these hills who are attuned to the spirit of the beast. I don't know if the tales are truebut I do wonder if you are not their kin.
A remarkable run. I expected the low-hanging vines of the swamps to cause some trouble, but not for you, I see!nnThat was a ride to rival the very best of the Black Horse Couriers!
I thought the ash clouds might impeded your visibility, but you mastered the challenge.nnExcellent. That is exactly the kind of focus the Black Horse Couriers are looking for!
Good work. Talk to my assistant Talaya, so she can record your time.
Go away! He'll get suspicious! Get the brazier!
What've you been up to? You vanished for a while. Any plots on getting behind the scenes?
It's time we got back, before the Lodge comes after us.
Skeleton Key looks nice up there, doesn't it?
It's still amazes me we stole from a Daedric Prince.
I can't wait to see what new faces we'll get.
Ah finally. We may begin.
Whenever you're ready.
Yes, yes. You'll do nicely.nnI have a task for someone with your abilities. A dangerous task, but very profitable.
May the Moons watch over you and always guide your steps.
We'll calm the water here for a while longer and mend what wounds we can. Return after you've found my missing guards and I'll pay you for your trouble.
You did it, Milksop! Speak to Atildel. She has something for you from all of us.nnGo on! You'll love it!
It's  it's you! I'm not sure what to say. I honestly didn't expect you'd be back.nnGlad you're alive. What happened down there?
You defeated the Serpent? How? We weren't certain he could be harmed.nnThis bears investigation.

Outsiders! Sniffing around our valley like hungry little goats. But this is Osh Ornim land, little goat. Iron Orc land!nnAway, little goat, or Lashburr will use its bones to pick ourargh! Flint and blood, don't make me yell. It hurts too much.
A missed opportunity little Brother. Let's return to the Sanctuary.
The decision is yours.
How did it go? Is it over?
Where to now, rescuer? I'm not leaving here without those spellplates. So you'd better lead me to them.
Have you found out anything about the keystone yet? Why are you out here?
You're back! And you have this Skooma-drinking grin on your face. Beat those cultists, did you? It's awfully Undaunted of you. You should celebrate. Buy something.nnNo, really. Give me your money.
You're back!nnI'm not disappointed. Just surprised.
Almost done? Quickly, now. This news cannot wait.
The Wrath of Sithis. Interesting that the Listener is starting this now. It will be a discussion for another time.
I doubt the Listener spoke to the Keeper before making this decision. It'll be interesting to see what happens when he returns.
I can't wait to see what this is about!
Perhaps you should be talking to Oosh or Varn.

You there! You can't go any farther. It's the Scaled Court. They've taken over the ruined city. They're tearing apart Skyreach Hold in their search for more nirncrux.nnUnless, of course, you've come to stop them. Could I really be that fortunate?
What a disaster! They came out of nowhere, the Iron Orc bastards!nnYou should talk to our caravan master, Scattered-Leaves. I'm too rattled to even think straight right now.
I'm still alive! Thank Tall Papa! And all of my limbs are still attached!

Damn, stinking Iron Orcs! They dragged away poor Camaarie! Ran me through and took her while I was bleeding!nnLook, you need to find her. And the others, too. Talk to Scattered-Leaves. He's the caravan master and I'm sure he'll give you a reward.
Don't you have somewhere to be?
The Listener said he had something very special for it. I do not doubt it'll be an adventure. It should smile more. My dagger could always help with that.
My matron used to say I had some Iron Orc blood running through my veins. I guess they wanted it back.
Could Veesk actually make it through this place on her own? It looks kind of dangerous!
Well, you certainly throw yourself into your work. Haven't seen that much Daedra blood in a while. nnI trust you've brought me some heads?
Who were you speaking to, just then?
Speaking to air. I will err on the side of hopeful that you were speaking to the Night Mother?
It's like summer out here, all the time. Almost wish my armor wasn't so heavy.
Apologies friend, many and fervent. I must be moving.
Well, there certainly are a lot of Orcs and trolls in here. Exarch Braadoth is the chief, after all.nnAm I babbling? I think I'm babbling. I'll try to hold it together so we can finish the mission.
Don't gimme that look! YeahI'm drunk. YeahI threw up a little over there in the corner. That doesn't make you better'n me! Yer just jealous of my  free-wheeling lifestyle. Bugger off!

It is my belief that Molag Bal's minions committed a great sacrilege in defacing those statues. Even for a Daedric Prince, that is simply too far.nnThe gods would see him humbled, and they will strengthen our sword-arms accordingly.
Finally, the Serpent defeated. He killed so many of the others, wrought such destruction on this region  I didn't think I would live to see it happen.
Free the prisoners. There's no need for any more of them to die in these foul spawning pools.

Beware. A great darkness infests the catacombs below and its dead no longer slumber.nnI hoped to consecrate the tombs, but the danger is greater than I imagined. Something calls to the dead. It drives them into a frenzy.
Set the six pedestals ablaze. Once the fires burn, the Thief can finish the ritual.
The triggers will summon a bridge of Aetherial energy. It can only be activated in the presence of Celestial power. That means Cassipia is close to achieving her goals.

Your name is spoken of with a mixture of fear and respect among the Scaled Court. I know what you have accomplished against my former comrades. Now I need your help to undo what those fools have done.

You have my deepest thanks  whoever you are. nnJust remember, we may not be able to refine pure nirncrux, but we can easily extract it from infused items. You'll have to take it from Iron Orcs, but it's not like anyone will miss them?
How'd that big bastard taste? Never had dreugh in butter sauce before. Was he gamey, or tender like his little cousins? Hah!
I can feel time passing us by. We will never see this moment again. Claim your reward.
The Legion Zero soldiers are more dangerous than they look. This one thinks they have been ensorcelled by Molag Bal. nnSo you be careful. Shaghila wants the saboteurs dead, not you.

You here to learn a craft? Don't worry, there's no cost involvedyour alliance pays me to teach the basics.nnOh, and you'll earn certification as part of the training. Then you can fulfill crafting writs. It's a great deal!

Now is not the time, my friend. I mean you no ill will, but if you don't leave me to my thoughts I will draw steel against you.nnI came here to remember her. I have to remember her. I've lost everything else. I can't lose her as well.
Mortal, this Celestial Guardian has one more obligation for you to fulfill.
I'm authorized to train and certify provisioners, alchemists, and enchanters. If this interests you, we should begin immediately.

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"Queen Ayrenn bids you welcome! Masters of the craft await you in <<1>>! New crafters shall be trained! Accomplished crafters will be certified! All at no cost to you!"
"ALL CRAFTERS, take heed! Master crafters currently offer free training for those new to a craft, and free certification for accomplished crafters!"

It's you! How many mercenaries did my husband feed into that Gate? No one was supposed to follow me here. Not my husbandnot you.nnBut perhaps I can use your strength to my advantage. Go on ahead. It's the only way out.
I will wait. But I will not wait long before I start shouting again.
Welcome. This one is pleased to see a friendly face in these dangerous times.nnPerhaps talk to <<1>>? His goods fill many needs.
I can see you are not Undaunted. Don't waste your limited time on Nirn standing where you're not wanted.
Welcome to the Undaunted enclave!

I need every soldier I can get, so don't charge off and get yourself killed. nnBe prepared before you go. The door to the Nobles District is one-way, so if you want to return, you'll have to come through the sewers.

I salute your courage, warrior. And if you kill my former clan brother, I will reward you. nnBe careful though. As a vampire, Otholug is dangerous, especially with his thralls. I suggest you bring strong allies of your own.
How fortuitous to meet you here. You'll never believe what Kireth's gotten into this time. I swear, she does these things just to vex me.
Well isn't this a strange place to meet a familiar face! It's good to see you again.

Well met, champion. I spoke to the king earlier about this matter, but he's indifferent, so I suppose it's up to you.nnKilling Mogbach the Ice Heart will weaken the Winterborn, but it won't end the siege. We're close though, if you'll help us.
I'll head back to Orsinium and meet you there. Remember to test the whistle. It does us no good if we don't know how it works.
Yes. Yes. Go on now. Get the potion and the bone. And the egg, of course. Mustn't forget the egg. I'll be upstairs. We'll conduct the ritual up there.
They're trickling back in. I don't know what you're doing out there, but I say keep doing it.
The pipes are beginning to cool. Good work and thank you.

I can't tell you how thrilled I was so see Shawaz come staggering up from the ice. I patched up his wound, and I think he's gonna pull through.nnWhat about the schematics though? He said you were probably too late.
Go on. Let me die in peace. You must see that my life's work is not lost.
Thank you, and be careful. I don't think the Orcs understand language anymore. It's probable they'll only think of you as a source of tasty meat.
Fascinating! It will take some time to completely master this device, but I can suppress the outer perimeter defenses for now. The quarry, I mean.

I'll be a Bosmer's arse. Queen Ayrenn said you'd pass this way, but I thought it was just horker-dung.nnI hear you've killed more people than the Knahaten Flu. I don't know thoughyou really think you're tough enough for the mountains of Wrothgar?
Rumors about your prowess were understated. I'm damn glad you came.nnI would be hesitant to challenge Mogbach directly without you.
Those things killed most of our clan and now he wants to send them to Orsinium?nnThe clans will never accept it. It will shatter what little unity there is among the Orcs.
Collect those water samples quickly! Our alchemists need to analyze them soon.
Be wary of this Legion Zero, my friend. nnThese are not ordinary Imperial soldiers. Coldharbour's influence has somehow empowered them.
Get going. I've got to look for more people.

Good day, friend. Or is it evening? So hard to tell down here.nnIf you're expecting me to thank you for killing my captors, you're setting yourself up for disappointment. I don't know why you people won't leave the riekr to live here in peace.
It is done. You are Blood-Kin and our chieftain.
Your courage is matched only by your generosity, my friend. You do more on my behalf than my own brother.nnOf course, that doesn't say very much, but well, I'm very grateful.
What are you? Some kind of vagabond? I have nothing to say to you.
First my brother. Now my sister. I assume you've come for me?
First my brother. Now my sister. I assume you've come for me?
First my brother. Now my sister. I assume you've come for me?

Oh, don't mind Kurog. He'll be all right. They just threw him into a fury. And who can blame him? Those dung-eating little brats don't deserve the title of chief.nnI'll talk to Kurog. Right now, there's something else we could use your help with.
Two combatants enter the fray, and Gloorig emerges victorious. Always suspected he would be chief one day. Doesn't make me any less proud.
fallthrough

It's time for you to face Clivia Tharn. I don't know what stake she has in this, but it can't be in the Empire's interest.nnYou'll find her through the portal ahead, at the top of White-Gold Tower. Divines go with you.
An empty crate sits here, waiting for a supply drop.
You here about the spoiled rations or something else?
Hmm. You're pretty clean for someone who's been slogging through the sewers. I'd at least expect to see a little blood on your gauntlets .nnWho'd you kill, anyways?
If you find any good mead out there, bring some back for me. I miss mead.nnDid you want something?

Well then, what are you waiting for? Go on. I'd offer you a blessing, but at this point, I don't think the gods even care.nnIf you really want a blessing, ask Valerianus over there. His faith certainly isn't wavering.
Rememberfind citizens, turn to torchbugs, return to Aishah, collect reward. What could be easier?
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.
YOU SHUT THE MAW. HAVE SOME POCKET CHANGE.
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.
YOU SHUT THE MAW IN AN ARBITRARILY DIFFICULT FASHION. HAVE A LORE JUSTIFIED BOX.

Come warm yourself by my fire, stranger. As the stones of this city grow colder, we must rely on each other if we are to survive.nnYou've been outside. Tell me, have the chains already pulled us all into Coldharbour?
You found them all! Mara's heart, I thought I'd never see them again, but here they all are!nnThank you!
The time is at hand. Stop second-guessing yourself, stop questioning your resolve, just stand up and do it. You're ready.
I know that this is a crucial mission. Just  just make it quick, all right?
How could Nadafa do this to me? And with a monster, no less! Oh, this is such terrible news!

<You notice a prominent handbill on the requisition board.>nn"Queen Ayrenn bids you welcome! Masters of the craft await you in <<1>>! New crafters shall be trained! Accomplished crafters will be certified! All at no cost to you!"
What's a friendly looking person like you doing in a place like this?
Dont get cocky now that you've beaten the first challenge. You're next match won't be easy. Get in there when you're ready.
Though you may think you have saved me from society, I have empowered myself to achieve my own success. You were but a pawn in that endeavor.
Go on ahead. I'll report to Sternis as soon as I'm able. Thank you again, my friend.

They say that Daedra never die. By Sithis, we will put that to the test. Shadows protect you.nnYou can use the door that leads to the Market District to bypass the sewers, but we must lock the door behind you. Make sure you're prepared.
Get down, fool. Enemies of the Pact are everywhere. If you want to make yourself useful, speak to General Hal-Rei in the sewer.

You're lucky. Whatever state the Arboretum's in, it's bound to be better than this skeever-hole.nnBe prepared before you go; the door to the Arboretum only goes one-way. To get back here, you'll have to go the long way, through those nasty sewers.
Imperial architectureha! I've seen Argonian muck-holes sturdier than this place. Go kill those saboteurs before they bring the whole place down on top of us!
You interested in gaining gold and glory? I'm signing up combatants for the next arena competition.nnDo you think you have what it takes?
If the Rat were you, he would try not to let the fleshy mess get too close. nnWhat if that condition is contagious?

You remember what you need to do, yes? If you go there and your alliance controls the district, it is easy. Just blow the horn. This one will send a runner to your silly boot-skin general. nnIf not, capture the district and then blow the horn.

I care not for the Covenant's ambitions, but I pray Onsi will guide your hand and that you will save us from the clutches of Coldharbour. nnIf you find the district is already under control, blow the horn to let me know. That would be very lucky.

Whatever's going on in the Temple, it can't be good. I'm glad it's you and not me going. nnNormally, I'd say that's a suicide mission, but after what you did here  I don't know, maybe I'll put my gold on you pulling it off. Maybe.

Shh! Damn it. Can't you see I'm trying to be subtle here? Subtle. That means I don't want to get noticed. nnI'm trying to rescue my brother, but I can't very well do that if the Daedra see me, can I? No. I can't.
Go see Ralen Veri. He'll set you up with our  organization. Then we can do business.
Psst! Hey you!
Hmm. You don't look like an outlaw, but you look like outlaw material.nnGo see Ralen Veri, if you want to make some extra coin.
Psst! Over here!
Yes, yes, you'll probably do fine. Go see Ralen Veri. He'll tell you what we're all about.
Want to be a part of our rather lucrative operation? Of course you do! Ralen Veri will tell you all about it.
I'm not sure what he sees in you, but Ralen Veri was quite adamant. He wants to offer you a place in our organization. As hard as that might be to believe.
This one shall tell you a lucrative secret  Ralen Veri. He'll make you an offer you shouldn't refuse.
I have two words for you, lover, so pay close attention: Ralen Veri. He'll treat your purse quite well.
Sorry, can't help. Talk to Ralen Veri. Let him decide if you're outlaw material.
You there. Yes, you!
This one isn't allowed to speak with you. Find Ralen Veri. Let him decide if you belong in our organization.
You there! Come here!
I only deal with members of  an exclusive club. If you want to know more, talk to Ralen Veri.
Psst! This one has searched all over for you.
You didn't hear it from me, but Ralen Veri can set you up. He's connected to all kinds of tempting opportunities.
Fresh meat, eh? Think you can beat me?nnHeh! Just kidding. We haven't made anyone duel to join the Enforcers in years. Those were the days.

As I feared, we arrived in different locations. I am in a city of industry, where men speak of intrigues and plots beneath layers of innuendo and pleasantry.nnIt matters not. You have awakened once again and we must set you on your path.
You've been of great help to us, friend.
You know what? I'm honestly surprised. I just didn't think Julien had it in him.nnBut this necklace  I've never seen the like. Now I know. This is what love feels like.
I feel much better about leaving now. In fact, I feel proud.
How goes the investigation?
Gardening is difficult enough without fending off goblins.
Averos sent you to me? Excellent.
I agree with Canning that you must visit Thrandor's Portla - but I would ask for your help first. Anything you accomplish at the portal will be for naught if Camlorn falls.
You're not a bad person, for an adult. I like you.
Another soldier was just brought back from wandering.  Have you had any luck with the will-o-the-wisps?
You have your task. Return when you've completed it.
Who are you and what do you want?
How are you faring against the undead wolves? Beware: the vile things are cunning and diseased.
To reclaim our great tree, we must first cleanse the poison gnawing at its roots, but it will not be easy.
In his note, Tamarus had asked if Coldun would have any reason to march upon Alaygon, other than that of the Camaroot? Oh they have reason all right, and it chills me to the bone.
The Prophet was right! This village will be destroyed.. what will we do?
We are under attack! Whatever you've done has appeared to put Coldun on the offensive. Normally I would say good job, but we need to get the innocents out of here first! Go! Now!
With the relics in hand, we must perform the ceremony immediately. The storms I sense beyond the Mundus worry me.
You will find Magus Commander Vistra near the northern end of Aldcroft. She's near the training targets.
What is it? I'm afraid we've got a bit of an emergency at the moment.
You've done all the hard work. I'll finish cleansing the tarn. I'll make sure the purification is complete.
Elbert sent you? Good man.
Gloria suspects Faolchu's agents are here among us, even now.
Ah, it's Shava's helpful friend.  What can Shava do for you?
I can't say I'm thrilled about having to arrest Moreau, but at least Thierry has his damned ring back, right?
You're welcome to use my extra fishing poles. Good luck!
I'm sure Lord Alain's just fine! Then again, it never hurts to check. He's getting old, you know.
You have done well the bring the lurcher back to us. The sacrifice is complete.
You've honored my sisters. This means so much to us, <<1>>. Thank you.
Warden Broles is doing what he can to help our men, but please see if you can help him.
I don't know who to trust any more, that's for sure.
Thanks to your help, my job is now eaiser.
Assist Telenger at the coast near The Pearls, to the southwest of my Kinhouse. We may speak again later.
I do hope the Altmer soldiers wielding Opalescent poisoned weapons don't nick themselves. I  know of no antidote....
Sload may be responsible for the dead rising from the sea. Have you discovered any of their Larva Sacs in the waters to the southwest?
Have you brought back the Irradiant Jewel from the Landbreaker? Check the spyglass on the ship's bow.
Stay not your arm - we must recover the Varla Lens from Hainen. Go to his Sanctum at the north end of The Imagerie, and take it from him.
You have found Meteoric Glass? Splendid!
I have need of an embassy to the priestesses of Mara.
Limwe found you, did she? It is rare to find one as reliable as she.
Optimate. I must presume you have acquired a Blessed Bell - else you would not intrude upon my meditations.
That is not the face of one who has met success. May I assume the Oyinaam is down?
Camlorn will be free, soon enough.
I can now help you retrieve the Varla Lens.
The Fragment of Orgnavar fell to the northeast of here. Destroy it and fetch me some of the debris.
Have you checked on my soul gem?
Greetings, Numinous. Your young charge has already reported in.
Poor Apothecary Bella. She struggles to remember what works and what doesn't.
The foxglove nectar in the liquid silver will draw the poison more quickly through the soldier. It's the best cure.
Please hurry. Take the Imbued Stones to the shore and place them on the Quo-Plinths!
Ready now? I warn you, you must be precise. A moment's miscalculation and we shall be forced to begin the forging anew.
Quickly, my dear Optimate, light the candles!
The Maormer ravage the sky as they do the land.
Nirn is restored, yet the Orrery is incomplete. The planet Auri-El was knocked from the sky by the hateful Maormer. I would ask more of you, fine <<1>>.
The Maormer added an intruder planet to our Orrery. We must discover it purpose.
You have interfered enough. Optimate, I will send you to your grave.
A book from Suuniqwe?
I've many weapons to bless and little time to do it. Thank you for your help.
I shall be more mindful of the wind in the future.
In your hands, the Midnight Talisman obiviously holds great power. What has happened, <<1>>?
I'll never forgive the Blackhand Cultists for the horrific things they've done to us. nThank the Divines you're here. You've really hindered their plans.
Do you know anything about what happened at the mine? No one can tell me anything!
How did it go at the ruins?

The rats aren't themselves right now. The sooner those chickens are gone, the sooner my work can continue.nnFortunately,  the cats don't seem interested in my rats. They're too busy snacking on the local catnip, I suppose.
Despite all obstacles, the Varyllis Varline is restored to full power! High Kinlord Langdruun will be overjoyed - please report to him.
Ho there, Numinous! I hear the battle goes well.
Great tragedy! Horrid fate! Al'kari's chickens, Al'kari's children, all gone! Al'kari will never trust again.
Have you managed to thin the Gem Spider population, Optimate?
So Old Man Murrell finally sent me some help! Well met, <<1>>.
What news, Optimate?

I have examined the limbs you collected from the feral Spriggans - magic has tainted it, thick with corruption. I worry for High Rock. Worse, if the Great Elum exists, this corruption has likely driven it mad as well.
Some of us are more sensitive to disturbances in the Varlines. My mother is among those.
I have inspected the harp.
Isque has dispatched their Emissary, Numinous. Your efforts bear fruit.
Stay wary. The Maormer grow bolder with each passing day.
There are too many casualties. We need more mages skilled in the school of Restoration.
Ah, you have come. I have been so lonely here in this cold shrine. Perhaps we could kindle a fire.
Shrine is dull. Want space to run. Want it painted red.
Have you tried the device yet? Which way did the thief go?
Welcome to The Orrery, Optimate.
I can't send my own guards. nnThere's a plot brewing, but you... you can go.nnOh, Lakana. My Lakana....
I heard. I can't believe Lakana is dead. nnI hope you'll find her murderer... and I hope you'll make him pay.

My job is protecting travellers on the main road. nnI'm diverting people who want to cross the farms as a shortcut. You can see from here that it's too dangerous.nnYou don't think I've been sent here to die, do you?
Wait! What about Rozenn! Was that real, or was it just a dream?nnWhere is she? Do you know? I think it was real. You! You have to help me!
Get the true name out of the Glenmoril Coven or go slaughter some Daedra. It's up to you... just don't delay.
Please hurry. The longer we wait, the more of my people will fall prey to starvation  or worse.
You look like you can defend yourself. Welcome to Camp Tamrith.

I admit, I had my doubts, but you've proven yourself time and time again. You're not only a worthy ally, but also one whom I can trust.nnI have yet to figure out the Altmer, but if he is an ally of yours, I will not turn him away.
Do not keep Durak waiting. He is the busiest of us all, and I fear for what the fervor is doing to Menevia.
So many people have somthing to gain from the death of Duchess Lakana.nnBoth Redguards and Bretons may profit from her untimely demise.
The mages sent to <<1>> were my friends.
You managed to save one of the nereids.nnYour actions please Merida!
Convinced Colane Oscent to let that ship unload, eh? nnWell, I hope we won't regret your meddling in our affairs.
My father said the Daedra are causing our problems. He said we shouldn't trust anyone.
Were my efforts for naught? Have I failed the people I tried to save?
Perhaps I deserved this fate. nnPerhaps I've broken the laws of my people, and the Eight are looking down on me in spite. nnMaybe this is my destiny.
We don't tolerate criminal activity. Watch your step.
With every moment that passes, there's less of my brother to bury.

If you've come to Firebrand Keep to petition for help from the Knights of the Flame, I'm afraid you'll be disappointed. nnOur leader, Sir Hughes, seems to have gone mad, and the knights are divided over whether or not to follow his last order.
What news, friend? Your countenance is rather somber.
If you can spare a few moments, my master would like to have a word with you.
I am proud to see you wearing that amulet, <<1>>. nnAll now know you as Hammerdeath's finest gladiator!nnHave you come to prove your mettle yet again?
It's time for me to return to Pariah Abbey and face what I've done to Master Ahtah.
I trust you to return with news of Fahjiri, whether good or ill. Be safe on your travels.
Thank you for your help.nnJulien is easily distracted, but I love him all the same.

I should have known Scarlette would try something drastic. After all, I did so myself many years ago.nnIn time, she will mend. I can only hope the dark magic's hold on her heals along with her wounds.

Lieutenant! Where in Oblivion have you been? Those damn sleep scrolls were useless against the brutes! The Orcs breached the walls, and we're down to just a few dozen men, including the King's Guard. nnI'm afraid it may be time to surrender.

S'rashi has marked where you can find these debtors on the map. Start with the gambler, Louis Ervine. nnErvine owes S'rashi the most money. S'rashi needs money from the others too, but search for them after Ervine.
Go on inside.nnHer Ladyship wouldn't want you to miss any of the "fun."
Go on inside.nnHer Ladyship's been missing you.
Will you acquire the Wyvern Egg and trade it for the Moonbird?

In creating the Plane Merge, the Dark Council has prevented anyone with cursed blood from entering.nnHowever, this doesn't stop us from using our glyphs to reach those planes. The wards are already in place. We just need you to do the rest.
No. This can't be happening. nnNot Mathias. He wouldn't have stomped on a diseased rat, let alone hurt a person .
Did you find it? For the offering? Did you find what we need for the offering?nnWe must have it.
We've all been damned by what happened at Crestshade. nnI've... come to terms with that.
<<1>> asked for you.nnShe believes you're capable enough for a delicate task.

My dreams spoke of you, as well. I knew a stranger would arrive and free those held in the bindings of evil!nnThis has all come to pass. The fate of Shornhelm is drawing near. We must take great care not to rush its conclusion, lest we awaken.
I wish I could return for a short time to see my family.

I will personally bring word of Farah's death to her brother.nnThere is nothing more for you here, <<1>>. I suggest you seek out Razorvine Refuge to the east.nnOffer what aid you can. If you crave revenge, drive back the Imperials.

Before you duel Grul, I have a message from my master, the Midnight Phantom. nnYou intrigue him. He wants to play ... a game.nnThere's an abbey to the north. Go there and do what you will. If you survive, we'll see you again.
There you are! Have you seen Heloise? Some of the Hinaults have arrived, but I haven't seen Heloise since she ran off with her healing kit.
To survive such a conflict... lose those we love... I must show a stoic resolve. Represent strength to these frightened people.
Shh... the Forest has ears, ya know.
