One thing you can always count on after a battlelots of extra weapons.nnI saw some of the soldiers tossing weapons into the barn. You should be able to find everything Gennove asked for in there.
Root around in Marienne's possessions and find whatever else she stole! The dead won't rest until we set things right in the Barrow.
You really overpowered my graverobbers? You intrigue me more than I ever imagined.
This is not a good time for the Knights of the Flame to be divided.
That little game was fun while it lasted.
We are on all sides besieged.
The stench of death lingers upon you. Have you been to the haunted plateau then? Where is the traitor Sorcassil?
You need to know more?
I never thought I'd see the day when Firebrand Keep was divided. These are dark times indeed.
I hope you can help us finish off the Fellwatch.nnAs long as they're stirring up trouble, Fell's Run can never be unified.

The Fellwatch are cunning opponents. They know the best way to conquer is by dividing, and trust has always been lacking in Fell's Run.nnThey're clever, but I doubt they can outwit a sword. Show no mercy. You'll find their camp north of Fell's Run.
You have the glyph. Quick! Take it to Sorcassil at the Thalmor.

Whatever they've found that's keeping the remnants active is far greater than any power I've felt before. nnDon't hold back in there, <<1>>. These battles will test our will to live. We must win. All of Rivenspire, and much more, depends on it.
I'm not sure what you've done or how you managed to do it, but Tristan's signs are already improving.
We'll keep Nialyn hidden until we can arrange to send her to safety. Her mother is in Elden Root.
My request was clear, I trust? Deliver digging tools to each of the loyalists up in Leaftower.
I've been told the Nord commanders have taken to their longboats and started sailing for distant waters.nnWhatever soldiers remain will soon scatter or fall to our blades.
Did you find Mathias? I hope he hasn't left town or anything.nnIt would  break my heart if I lost him as a manservant.
Thank you for speaking to Jolie, stranger. nnI do hope she is willing to hold on a little longer. We can beat this I know it.
Whoever planted that amulet on one those creatures wants play a cruel joke on me.nnI do wonder if that villain will find it humorous when his body floats into the sewers with my blade in his back?
I do not know how much more of this I can take but I don't want to end up like Mul and the others.
Whoever planted my amulet on those creatures wants to play a cruel joke on me.nnI wonder if that villain will find it humorous when his body is found in the streets with my blade in his gut?
Are you prepared to face the horrors of Cold Harbor?
Are all of the scarecrows up? The one here looks very grim. I hope it works.
Good luck in there. I don't envy you one bit for heading into that dark place. nnI promise you, my men will be shortly behind, securing the ground you take. You'll be an inspiration to our soldiers.
My friend, have you considered my position in this Nord business? nnI'm sure you can understand my concern for the well-being of Northpoint.
Ahh, poor deranged Hainen. I was once his pupil, you know.
Do you think she can hear me? This Optimate is going to help you, Mistress!
Nimbleberry bushes grow under the dome at the northern end of the Imagerie.
Isrisa! She... I watched her... a cat!
Are you ready for my first riddle?
Thank you for your aid. Now that we have Treethane Selyin's body we will be able to eat his sin so that he may be forgiven by the Valenwood.
We have already visited Isque and The Orrery, have we not, <<1>>? It seems we must proceed to Dusk, far to the east. nnThat shall be quite a walk, I fear.
Thank you for finding a sample of that poison. Now we can save my men.
We have yet to gain the loyalty of High Kinlady Genivra in The Orrery. It seems our last stop will be there, <<1>>.nnGo on ahead of me. I shall meet you in the Scintilla Kinhouse.
It seems our last stop will be in Dusk, <<1>>.nnGo on ahead of me. I shall meet you in the Scintilla Kinhouse.
It seems our last stop will be in Dusk, <<1>>.nnGo on ahead of me. I shall meet you in the Scintilla Kinhouse.
If you can confirm the rumors of Montclair's allegiance with these... vampires... I will regard you as my most trusted ally. nnKnow that House Dorell will not take kindly to this.
If Montclair thinks to take my citizens and use them against me, he has sorely underestimated me.
Eh? What do you want? Don't think you can sneak up on me.nnWhatever it is, make it quick.

Govran's always been in one trouble or another, but I can assure you, it's purely out of high spirits. nnHe isn't even a man yet. He's not the type to purposely destroy another man's property.nnI know my own brother, don't I?
You're back! Tell me you have some good news.
One day, when I'm not wounded, I hope we can fight side by side.nnPerhaps that day, we can chase these deceitful Daedra away together!
Colane Oscent thinks we're out to get him. He just doesn't trust us.
<<1>>, my lady Lakana would have blessed you many times over for what you've done. nnPlease accept my humble expression of gratitude.
There is so much to rebuild, it's hard to know where to start.
We will soon reclaim what little ground the Imperials still hold to the west of Southpoint.
Damn the Imperials! They have Farah! nnFor every three I slew, another five came at us. I was overwhelmed and unable to help the girl.nnYou must save her. We cannot let another thane be slain.
That woman in the stocks... she's one of them. One of the Wyrd! She did this to me! nnWithout my wedding ring, I'm not safe from her spells!
She's missing... missing and cannot be found!nnThey did this to her. They did it, and they'll come for me next. nnJust you watch. They will!
Khajiit don't fare well in water. The fur gets heavy. It takes forever to dry, and until it does, we smell funny.
I'm keeping an eye on things for my father. nnI've got a job to do. I shout a warning if we need to run to the village.nnThe way those folks treated my aunt, though, I doubt we'd get a warm welcome.
The sailors will be glad to have some shore leave.nnI don't know whether they'll enjoy Koeglin Village, though. It's too... peculiar... right now.
Recapturing Southpoint was yet another victory for the Dominion. Praise Queen Ayarynne!
I recognize this soldier.  Do you have word of Fort Arand?
Your need must be urgent if the Hortator deigned to return from his eternal rest in Othrenis. nnPlease respect his sacrifice. Make your request brief.
How did you fare with the cliff racers?  A few less is still progress...

I hope you don't travel to Alcaire Castle only to find it under siege. If that is the case, I have made a grave mistake.nnLook for Dame Falhut though. Hopefully, the Redguards have simply come here in a diplomatic capacity.
You are swiftly making a name for yourself here, Clanfriend.  The Initiate has not stopped talking about you.
You wonder why I send you on errands when you search for the Blight? Trust Sugar, and you will see why.
What can Sera Orvona do for you?
I, Ahjiivi, thank you for ridding the town of those shaveskinned slavers. Ask, and Ahjiivi will help you find this Blight.
"Noises in the woods," they say. There's nothing but noises in the woods! It's full of animals, for Y'ffre's sake!
Come now, we'll have time to talk when you return. Go now, and entertain my friends!
Soon, I will rest. Soon, I will find peace.
Would you like to dance with us? Come now, don't be shy. I don't bite... much.
The Grahtlord presented us with a difficult choice.nnI hope they haven't made a meal out of those slain animals from the Thrambles.
I can't believe how warm the mud is! And they say it has curative properties. Imagine that!
There will be time for work later. We'll attend to business later... once we're done with the business of pleasure.nnI'm very diligent about my business.
Why rebuild? Even if I had the strength to try, I do not have the money for supplies.
General Cruor and his men ravaged our town! And then they cut down Mara's Grove to build their palisade.
Welcome, traveller. Do you come here often?
I won't tarry here much longer, but it's really quite pleasant.
Bring these transgressions to the Tribunal's attention. nnWho knows how deep the corruption runs?
Speaking with the winner of the scavenger hunt.nnExclaiming great joy!nnOffering congratulations!
No more distractions! I must think. nnWhat is the most expensive and extravagant gift I could provide for my darling <<1>>? nnWhat would give her the most pleasure? What would make her happy?
Reywell has cured me of my despair! nnIt doesn't matter whether I sleep or not while I'm here.
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything.
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
I'm ready for anything!
The deliciousness of the failure of Wud. The savoring of your victory. Hoom admires your achievement.
The courage of the victor! The well-deserved congratulations.nnPraising the stranger!
Let's get you into your new chausses.
What are you waiting for? Get back in there!
Colovians always think I run a worm farm. Idiots. A worm farm is for worms, and a maggot farm is for maggots.nnUntil the Imperials invaded, I had the biggest maggots in Valenwood - three feet long.
It's bad enough the Imperials take our homes. Did they have to slaughter our thunderbugs too?
It seems you're on to something much larger than the corruption in my office.  Keep following the trail, my friend.
Thanks to you, we have resources again... and fewer Ashlanders to fight. nnLuck be with you on your journies, friend. nnHopefully when you return, Senie will be more hospitable.
Helene sent you? Thank the Divines, you've brought the limbs.
Just get close to the netchlings. Give 'em a poke with the stick I gave you. They're docile enough after that.nnWhen you get a handful, bring them back here. I'll take it from there.
Thank you again for all you've done for us here in Ebonheart.
I want to be alone. Please....
Vivec grant us justice! Punish these crimes! nnWhat you say is true, <<1>>.
I think we're all going to die. What about you?
I don't know if we'll be able to hold off an assault. What if they bring catapults?
Have you made the delivery?
Those wolves aren't going to skin themselves. Get those hides.

<<1>>! It is good to see you that you have blossomed under my tutelage.nnIt is a shame that we were unable to explore your soul together. nnBut never-mind. Go to Wayrest to seek out deep mysteries of our craft.
I'll move on. Just allow me a moment to lament my foolish ways. I never should have fallen for a man like Galas.
We really need physical evidence. nnWe can't report back to the Tribunal Temple with a bunch of half-formed theories.
Reme's the best healer in Glenumbra. nnDon't let anyone tell you different.
Goody Mester had this same cold and died from it, but I'll be fine. I don't know what I would have done if not for Reme's cures.
Now, about those bones you collected...
It's good to see you, <<1>>. You will always be welcome in our glen.
The alit can be found to the west of here. That one should hasten in its footsteps and bring me back those samples. If my suspicions are true, warnings will need to be given to the others...
Stop giving Lallae jagga, will you? She can't handle her drink.nnA column of timber mammoths could march by without her noticing.
If any of these creatures show signs of infection, considering the consequences would sadden me.nnI prefer not to think about that.
Omaynia is under our control, and we will fight until we have no strength left to keep it.
My sister, Llira, was always his favorite. nnShe doesn't even care that our father passed and left us with nothing.
Haven't you bothered me enough?!
My friend, you are back! What may this humble servant of Almsivi do for you?
Get a drop of the purple potion, a pinch of reagent and then combine them with the bergamont seeds in the alchemy set.
I grieve for those who died, but at least I'm alive to mourn them.
I grieve for those who died, but at least I'm alive to mourn them.
I grieve for those who died, but at least I'm alive to mourn them.
I grieve for those who died, but at least I'm alive to mourn them.
I grieve for those who died, but at least I'm alive to mourn them.
In time Gil-Var-Delle will return to Valenwood, starting with Black Log.
You might as well turn ri- hic! Right around. And go back where you came from.
My wife is a skilled hunter. nnShe's been getting our child used to the idea of prowling the forest.
Wear my mask and slay the Orcs in Karthdar to the north, then set their bodies aflame.
Ordinator Faydile Slythin is on the docks north of here.nnHe's keeping a close eye on the ship inspections.
Invigorating! I'm ready for anything now! nnMaybe I'll set out to Davon's Watch. I've had enough with this farm life... especially since Lluthyne's out of good, strong drink!
With your help with those kwamherds, we may yet make it back into the mine.

My brother Raynor and I left the city when the blight hit. nnWe decided to chase our dreams instead of simply sitting around waiting to get infect. nnThus, we set out to explore the ruins of the world! We set out to experience an adventure!
Yes, I pray to the Dunmer gods. nnWho else has the power to save them, besides the deities they worship so reverently?
What news do you bring?nnDid you find <<1>>?
There is no time to waste! Race north to Vulkwasten and tell Voheria Thornthicket that the Wild Hunt was loosed upon Cormount.
What have you done? nnDidn't I tell you to leave well enough alone?nnIt had to come to this eventually, I suppose.
Thank you for all you've done for me.nnPlease let me mourn for a while.
Thank you again for helping me. nnI now have enough ash reeds to make tea for everyone suffering here.
My only regret was that I could not do the deed myself. nnI guess I can live with that. nnI'm in your debt.
There is no rest to be found in Vulkwasten, <<1>>.
You must collect Lifetimber Flowers from the Lifetimber sapling to the northwest.
I'd keep your actions to yourself, if you care to stay healthy.nnThat's not a threat from me. That's advice from someone who's felt the sting of House Dres.
Please speak to Prince Aeradran. Tell him he is free to assault the Feladrim.

Remember; keep your distance until you can get a clear path to the braziers. The Ashlanders might look the innocent type, but you disgrace their Prince and they'll stomp you. This of course would cause quite a commotion and that's not what we want.
The Dres are in your debt. nnHopefully, this will silence those who speak ill of our Great House... at least for a little while.
Is the town still burning?nnNo one will ever return to Moira's Hope if the town is still on fire!
The Sapiarch is the one binding the spirits to these ruins.
We've done all we can to rally the soldiers, at least for the moment.
I don't expect to stay here for long. The Peatwalkers will send someone to burgle me back soon enough.nnIt's nice to be wanted, but all this walking is certainly tiring.
Thank you! With your help, we'll be able to stay here much longer. We can endure anything the elements bring to us.nnAs soon as he calms down, I'm going to take all our ale and dump it in the bog.
Now that the birds are restored, we must find my betrothed!nnWe must find Therese!
Now a grim task falls to you: stop this undead abomination before it leaves a trail of dead through Glenumbra.
Were you able to protect <<1>> from the spectres?
Unbelievable. Summoning Daedra in my house! Stupid, selfish girl.
I do apologize for sending you on such a wild goose chase. A mother can't help but worry for her kin.
You are a spiteful person, you know that? After I begged you not to tell... you try and ruin me anyways!
A chicken, you say? I guess it wasn't Akatosh after all.
A chicken! Well, I'll get Valdam to undo it. Eventually.
The spirits are still quite angry, but I no longer feel that anger directed towards my people. nnWe must be patient. The ancestors will care for us.
Now that we got the crew out safely, next order of business is to get back to sea.nnI'm betting we'll have better luck finding a ship in Wayrest than back in that little village.
Poor <<1>>, all alone! It would be cruel of me not to offer him comfort. I know! I'll make him a pie. Yes, a pie for my true love.
You have completed the first part of this trial. nnHead down the hall to start the next challenge.
I still feel quite weak.nnI must rest a bit before I can return to my farm. I'm sure my wife will be glad to see me.nnThen again, if she knows what I've been after, she probably won't be so glad.
Thank you for helping <<1>>, but it's Murk-Watcher that worries Dro-Dara now.nnTime seems to have softened Murk-Watcher's mind. She often is being very confused and very stubborn.

Ah, the young adventurer again. You remind me of the old days. So many stories I could tell, but you'll want to be leaving, of course. nnWell, we might be heading out too. Janne might be right about a curse here. Speaking of Janne, have you seen her?
This life is not the one for me. Star-crossed should be my name.
My friend! Please stay in the cave. Wait for the fight. nnIt'll just be a few minutes.
We heard the cave collapse from here. I was wondering if you'd made it out alive.
You have it? Give it to him.nnI will watch and pray.

I'm sure there are souls in those gems. Even now, I can hear them.nnI don't know why they're being held. I don't know what end it serves, but it's not right. They're in torment. Please, you must aid them.
Finish what we started. If I die, I want to die knowing we got rid of the ogres. nnIf I live  well, I'm not gonna live long with all these ogres around anyways.
Too many deaths, and everyone is too slow. Running wild wouldn't do much good, though.nnI may have need of you, but not quite yet.
What does the contract say? You should read it.
I will have the Codex examined. You carry on, and we shall meet again in Wayrest.
I knew I liked you when you started scrambling up here like an Amberberry-drunk Imga.nnNot graceful, but determined.
I hope you've made sure he's busy rewriting that report.
Superlative day! Your aid against the Imperials has been most advantageous.
<You stand before Tedril's lifeless body.>nn<The pain that once defined his face has been replaced with peace.>
Though my father is dead, I can at least take comfort in knowing his suffering is at an end.
I fear Dalo may never wake from his nightmares. nnI do not know what power has taken him from me. nnThis must be the work of those unholy ashlanders!
Behind the temple is a great waterfall. nnGo beneath it. Go behind it. Find the hidden entry to the temple.
You've returned, my friend!nnAs you can see, we have yet to drive these dogs from our lands. nnWe must bide our time... and strike when we can.
We're faced with nothing but trouble these days.
I have to admit, I wasn't sure a <<1>> like you would care about defending Narsis. First impressions aren't always correct.nnAs long as I'm here, you're welcome in the council chambers.
For the tribulations this war has inflicted upon Falena, I will fight without mercy!nnI will be a slave until they cut me down upon this bloodstained battlefield!nnOnly then will I truly be free.
Well? Was I right? nnWas it as I predicted, <<1>>?
The ogres' leader is called 'Skull Crusher'. He's big, he's mean, and he's nasty, but you can take him.nnI would send soldiers to help you, but another battle is brewing, and they have to prepare.
Those prisoners have been through so much. nnI'd hate to have them end up as casualties during an attack.
I was foolish to think I could keep up this facade for very long.nnI thought I was fooling others, but I was only fooling myself.
Letters from the Iliath Temple are rare, but always of great importance. nnThank you for the safe delivery of this missive.
Bestowing warm appreciation for your efforts. nnEnjoying the pleasure of your acquaintance!
Wud is enjoying your company! Wud will invite you to sit with him.nnThe delight of friends laughing. The dismissal of woes.
You have done more for me than I can ever repay.
Placing the relic in the Obelus will take some time. nnPlease, let Narsis know of our progress here. nnBy the time you return, we hope the Obelus will be restored again.
You must free the sick captives. They may be ill, but they don't deserve to suffer at the hands of the Vereansu.

Hail to you, champion of the North. I am glad to see you have survived the trials set out by my brothers. You have proven your faith.nnI cannot wait to hear your tale. How was it you were brought here to our refuge?

The next fight will be more of a challenge. It's a test of your situational awareness. nnRemember to control your anger. Watch your surroundings. nnYour enemy may not be your true target. Never forget that!

The next fight will be more of a challenge. It's a test of observation.nnRemember: don't let rage control you. Be aware of your surroundings. nnYour enemy may not be your true target. Always remember that!
You have done more for me than I can ever repay and yet I must ask for your assistance one last time.
Have you found the caps? I need more caps.

Whatever they've found that keeps the remnants active is far greater than any power I've felt before.  nnDon't hold back in there, <<1>>. These battles will test our will to live. We must win. All of Rivenspire, and much more, depends on it.
Sarvyl takes such good care of me.nnWhere am I?

Delay in your appointed task, and I will feed to the scamps!nnTo rise within our ranks, one must complete the tasks laid out before one.nnYou should feel honored to have been bestowed with such an important mission.
When we activate these shards, the portal to the Daedric temple will open.nnAre you ready? This is so exciting! So dangerous! nnMostly dangerous for you, but really exciting for me!
Have you talked to that useless husband of mine yet?
May the Eight bless you for helping us. nnPlease, find my Arcady.
Do you come here often?
My friend, I'll be sure to save you some of our salt rice harvest.nnMy wife makes a fine salt rice stew. It warms you from the inside out!
You're not afraid. Try it out. Tell me what happens.nnWatch out for the claws.
I'll miss Shaleen. When we were kids, we played under the same branches.nnI didn't think we'd ever be separated.nnI'll mourn his passing.
I should be on my way, I believe. nnI do hope those witches below us are lax on their watch again.

I'm sure she'll never know the difference. You'll find Lady Diane Gedanis at Reywell Hot Springs, west of Wayrest.nnWhy did she send me to bring her wine anyway? Servants aren't allowed at Reywell! It's beyond me.
I've always trusted Priest Arves' judgment.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?
<<1>> is a good friend of mine. I'm certain he speaks the truth.
I hope those rumors turn out to be nothing but paranoia.nnSo, did you get those hides yet?
I hope this attack is isolated. nnIt may be a while before we can instill a level of confidence back in our people.
Strangeness surrounds us! It is the Balac you bear, but I expected something... different. Here, give it to me. I must examine the staff.
May your journey to Mournhold be a safe one.
If it's to be a fight, then I'd better prepare to give the best fight we can.
You won't regret helping Lord Sorick. He always remembers his friends.
The pain that once defined Tedril's face has been replaced with peace.

You have done well. Take the totem to the Coiled Shrine north of here. Complete the circle.nnWe no longer lay claim to our souls. We live in service to the Ghost Snake, enduring in return for its blessings. nnAll must return to the Coil.

I appreciate your assistance, but I would not want you to think of the Spirit Wardens as helpless.nnWe are a capable lot, but to be attacked out of nowhere like this, and by the Midnight Union  we were just caught off guard.
Seek out the King in Wayrest and give him the news. He must know as soon as possible.
I imagine Abbot Durak has a plan to recover the Dream Shard. And I'll wager you're involved.
You look as if you've had some luck.
Back from the Canulus Refuge! Were you successful? Did you get the staff?
You look pretty dangerous. Consider yourself drafted. nnThere are goblins here that need killing.
Help us complete the spell to fuse us once more, and we will reward you.
Help us complete the spell to fuse us once more, and we will reward you.

Half my men are obsessed with that Altmer queen. I guess she's nice. I mean, if you love that whole tall, blonde-haired, statuesque, well-endowed, ruby-lipped, shapely-calf-muscled....nnWhat was I saying?nnOh, yeah. She's all right, I suppose.
See that you succeed. My beloved doesn't like failure, and insists that I punish it. nnSeverely.
You were able to get the key to Destane's chest? I'm both impressed and truly thankful that you came along.
You've returned! I believe Barnabe and Geon have been busying themselves with swordplay. For awhile, all we heard was cursing and sword-clashing, but moments ago... silence.
I heard the commotion from here. nnWhat happened out there?

Speaking to you now as a friend, and as your king, I wonder if I might prevail upon you to assist me with some other matters.nnOne that is a matter of state, and another that is of a more  personal nature.
What!? Can't you let a man enjoy a moment's rest? nnOr does King Emeric need this bench right now?

<<1>> distracted the mercenaries so <<2>> could escape with his wife. The wife weeps for her husband, but this one is not good at comforting others, so <<2>> has watched over her from afar. nnYou look capable. This one would ask a favor of you.
Great job ridding us of those alit. nnThat makes life out here much safer for our patrons.
I have nothing to say to you.
Hey! You're standing on my dinner!
I certainly hope we don't encounter any more Daedra anytime soon.
I wasn't always like this. I had dreams as a boy.
The hoarvor mostly come at night. Mostly.
Yes? What business do you have here?
Come on, Jazha. nnCome on!
This is my lucky day. It has to be. It has to be.
This is my lucky day. It has to be. It has to be.
Come on, Shanari. Come on.
<<1>> is a good friend of mine. I'm certain he speaks the truth.
What's that? Parvaneh sent you? She's found a way out of meeting her obligations again, I see.nnI could use your help, though!
I smelled these cooking and just couldn't resist!
I smelled these cooking and just couldn't resist!
There's nothing like the smell of boar skins frying!
Are you ready to face the hoarvor? nnRemember: you must stay in the center ring.nnIf you're knocked out or you leave the ring, you'll lose by default.

I don't think the slavers knew what to do with the focusing crystals. Those may be close by. But the oilthey probably took that on board their ship.nnIf you can recover the supplies, I'll be ready to relight the fire. Godspeed to you, my friend.
Those prisoners have been through so much. nnI'd hate to have them end up as casualties during an attack.
You shouldn't be here!
They burned my stall! They burned my wares! I'll have to start over again. nnI can only salvage a few workable scraps from what's left.
Have you discovered the source of the rumors yet?

Arkay answered my prayers when he sent you here, <<1>>. You saved Rosalie from that Daedric beast.nnJust talking to you, I can feel my fear subsiding. nnIt's like... it's like a shaft of sunlight in the rain.
You return! And yet....nnFrom here, I can see the ones you treated are still afflicted.nnWhy does this magic not cure them? What demons possess them?

A catastrophe in Shad Astula! Misfortune caused by the taint of foreign magic! nnThat tree-licker was hired to teach "alternative" magic. She's disrupted the spirit of the Master Wizard!nnThat Argonian destroyed our great school! And you helped her!
Shad Astula is poisoning minds. Its source lies in its roots. nnTo cleanse the great tree, we must remind it of its greatness.nnEven you, who steals my things, should know that.
You've got quite a reputation. You helped the chicken farmer's wife recover her lost ring. I've heard all about it.
It is not safe for you here. Come, let us talk outside.
How's your hunt for the traitors going?
Do you dare to face the mighty ogre? nnGather your friends and petition Beastkeeper Onis. A lone warrior is doomed to fail!
Back for more?

So it's true what they say about you, <<1>>. nnYou have a way of hiding in the shadows, insinuating yourself into the affairs of others far greater than yourself.nnYou made it this far, meddler. I'm impressed, I dare say.
Perhaps we can help each other.nnYou and S'Rashi should work together.

I put some people back to work. nnThose... things... are still out there, but they seem rather innocuous. Hopefully, no one will get eaten. nnAt least we have new guar in the fields. We have you to thank for that!
If <<1>> ever shows his face here again, he's a dead man.
<<1>>! You are a hero of great honor. It is good to be free again.
Soon enough, the Bretons will get what's coming to them.
Come on, follow me. I'll introduce you to the rest of the staff.
Huh. That wasn't supposed to happen.
Thank you for what you have done for the Aralen family. I regret the loss of my brother, but his death is better than the family's destruction.
Leave me. I'm too injured to walk. At least I die knowing you took a few of those bastards out with you. You have my gratitude.
Even if Valentin isn't after my catch, who knows who else might be jealous of me? I must maintain constant vigilance!
I know the king will hear my summons soon! I feel it in my gut!
More fires? It's another attack!nnYou better tell Farmer Gaercroft right away.
What are you doing here? Only Apostle Marian is permitted in my sanctum. nnWhere is she? Didn't you give her the Water Stone?
Sometimes, I have to stop cataloguing artifacts just to look around this place.nnThen I can imagine what it was like at the height of its glory.

The greatest obstacle to translation is the language's inherent duality. nnThe Dwemer had two writing systems. One was for daily use, while the other was for philosophy and higher-order logic. nnThe latter form is almost impossible to understand.
J'raka is irrational and cruel. nnHis actions endanger the Warrior Guard.nnHe must be tamed.
Look! When the magic disappated, that portal appeared!
Do you think my parents would notice if I jumped?
You saved many lives this day. nnMay the moons shine on you, friend.

I will send guards to retrieve the body.nnIf it is indeed the remains of the Thane, the Bosmer people will want to handle the body accordingly. nnWe, however, have greater needs. We require information.
I wish I could return for a short time to see my family.
Hello again, <<1>>. Thanks again for making that delivery.
Why have you come back?nnThis is no mere chore to be done at your leisure! The Balac is the key to freeing this world from Molag Bal's grip. nnYou must find it with all haste.
Strangeness surrounds us! It is the Balac you bear, but I expected something... different. Here, give it to me. I must examine the staff.
Do you have the jewels with you?nnI am eager to perform the necessary rituals, not only for the safety of Elder Root, but also so we can leave this accursed place.

Ra'Vashi is eager to learn. One day, he will fight against the Imperials, risking his life alongside his brethren!nnPlease, tell this one how he should train. nnRa'Vashi wants to be a hero, but this one is unsure how to continue.
We will magically scry the area while you investigate.nnConsider yourself authorized to deal with anything appearing in the ruins.nnReport back to us once you have finished your reconnaissance.
Drink! Drink! Drink!
We're ruined, aren't we? There's not even enough of us left to tend to the farm. Do you think there's a place inside Evermore for a man and his dogs?
This explains why my rituals are not as effective. There is some greater problem at hand that needs a remedy before my simple cures will work.
Praise the Divines, my son will live!nnWhatever the source of the sickness, he's safe now. He's alive, thanks to you and Wyress Reinette!
She must send help! That Wyress told us she would bring help to Evermore, but all that's come here is death!
There are still entirely too many kwama about this place.nnI am... displeased.
If you want to get me another five claws, I wouldn't be opposed to buying them off you.
The statue and altar are north of here. You can follow the road to get there. I will remain behind. There is one final step I must take for this to work.nnHurry, <<1>>. She hasn't much time left.
I know Her Majesty's not herself lately. She's been so worried about King Eamond and Princess Elara.... I hope she chooses a Regent soon.
I don't feel very well suddenly.nnDo you think Evermore's plague was brought by the ghosts?
I supported Lady Ginie. Always have! I just couldn't go against the Queen's direct orders.nnGlad you got the Minister of War out of here safely.
The Princess will be missed. She would have made a great queen herself someday.
The Queen's sister will be a good Regent for Evermore.nnI think. Don't you?
This is a great day for Evermore. A great day for the Covenant!
You're here, just in time.nnWe ushered out the wolves you freed. I've no desire to see them turn on us again before we have our chance to disrupt the Reachmen.
These things have a way of working themselves out in the end. What we didn't collect from this ship, we'll collect from elsewhere.nnOr we can reduce some of the city's services.
My duties carry me back to Evermore. But someone must warn the nearby towns. There are many lives at stake.
What news from the priestess?
Thank you. Now, with nature's blessing, our little friend will survive the Reachmen invasion. nnBut as for her sisters  the only thing left is to avenge them.
I don't understand what's happened to Princess Elara, but at least Evermore's no longer under Lady Nadine's rule.nnNot that she did anything to hurt our finances, you understand.
I've heard the name of <<1>> from the tongues of our guar-herds. Is that you? nnThen hear my words. Take them into your heart.
The race will be starting soon. nnPlease be sure to wait nearby before the match begins.nnDo you have any questions about the race?
Have you learned what Vonov wanted to accomplish in his final ritual?
Focusing... must not... break the trance....
Praise the Eight! I can't tell you how delighted I am to see you. First, the Reachmen advance stopped, then the crows flew away, and now  you're back.nnI have a feeling you bring good tidings.
I hope Rothas didn't give you much trouble. nnDid you get any answers?
The Daedra seem arbitrary. They dispense boons as often as doom.nnThat doesn't make this fate any easier to bear.
Goodbye
Our herders have spoken of you. You protected our guar from nix-hounds.nnPerhaps you can also protect our village from the nobles' dogs.
There you are! What news do you bring me?

I've seen people begging the guards for mercy.nnI've seen strong men on their knees, crying and begging like Altmer women. nnI've seen people offer to trade the Kagesh money, power, or even their own bodies for a cure.nnWhat do these Ashlanders want?
I regret deceiving you. But had I told you I, a simple groundskeeper, was the descendent of one of the best known spirit hunters in Bangkorai's history, would you have believed me?
If you have any love for the Three, help us strike down these Kagesh!
I will carry out King Eamond's last command, no matter who stands against me.
I hope you found Methel. nnShe's persistent, so I imagine that disease will have a hard time breaking her.
Someone on the other side of the door speaks as you walk up to the door with the food.nn"Thanks for feeding us. We need more help, but first, you'll need to prove yourself trustworthy."
We keep to ourselves and hunt only animals. We don't harm humans.nnWe also offer sanctuary to anyone afflicted with lycanthropy.
Have you put out the fires? nnIt's hard for me to see through the smoke.

The Three are living Gods. To go against their will is unthinkable.nnConsider: if one of the Gods appeared before you, performed miracles, and asked for your faith, could denying them be anything other than evil?

You helped the Kagesh tribe before. <<1>> has said it on the wind. nnWill you now stand aside and let these heretics slaughter us?nn<<2>> showed as much mercy as he could muster. His men and his pretender gods know nothing of honor. Help us fight!
Don't tell me Rerynia is going to let you question this Ashlander. nnThe idea that she may trust what he has to say disgusts me.

The Ashkhan and I were never comrades, but we respected each other as combatants.nnSometimes my men would spar with his, and we would both celebrate the victor.nnThose were carefree times, <<1>>. I don't expect to see them again.
I'll ensure the undead do not attack while we finish the ritual. nnPlease, help Sir Dencent convince Father Hurrent to stand aside.
Enter text related to Fort Thendr
One day this shrine will be the glory of Morrowind.
We spent years rebuilding this shrine. nnI won't let them tear it down again. I'll die first.
I'll find you out there, <<1>>. nnKill as many Imperials as you can... and be careful.
<You hear the king's voice in your head.>nnIt's really rather strange seeing myself this way. One always thinks of one's self as young.
One last thing ... this is all I will ever ask of you ....
Grahtwood's troubles will end soon. So exciting! nnVonov has caused so many problems. He's taken so many lives. We must stop him... once and for all.nnWe can't let him channel the power of <<1>>!
You are honorable. I only ask one thing of you. nnPlease, let our Great Father know of this betrayal.nnTell him what I have told you. Then you may do with me as you will.

I was separated from my wife when we were taken. That was six months ago. I haven't seen her since.nnThe thought of her enslaved by some Dunmer.... that makes me want to punch one of them until he stops moving.
I've been here so long. I can't remember my parents anymore. nnI only vaguely remember the green grass of Glenumbra. I think it was green....
This one wishes he was elsewhere... maybe back home in Elsweyr.nnOh, wait! This one just got that. nnClever.

Many flyings of Jone and Jode have passed since this one could commune with them. nnThe Dunmer think moon sugar is a drug, so they won't let us have any.nnWhat ridiculous mer! The sugar is not for them! No wonder it makes their minds sick.
Look at my hands! They're calloused. The nails have chipped away! nnTo have me laboring like this is a waste of my prodigious intellect.
My hands will never be clean again.
I pray you find that salt. nnLet Onsi guide your blade.

Without King Eamond or reserves from Stormhaven, we can't possibly retake the garrison.nnThe Imperial Seventh Legion is strong, but returning to Evermore now means accepting failure. We must not fail.
They've taken <<1>> to the altar of sacrifice! Any chance for her to escape is about to go up in flames! nnWere you able to talk to her? What did she say?
Josselin  that is, Lieutenant Glenan  returned to her tent to rest. Turn to the south. Her tent is just to the right of the campfire.nnTell her what I told you. She'll know what to do from there.
Sounded as if you ran into a little trouble while conducting those interviews.
I'm going to stay with her. I wouldn't want scavengers or one of the Daedra to take her body.nnI need you to tell someone she's passed on. We need to have her blessed and taken to the <<1>>.
I know not why you have made your presence known, <<1>>, but I have nothing to say to your kind.nnI must ask you leave before I tear you apart.
I'll sleep better at night. nnSo will many others, I imagine.
I'll send some guards to the house at once.nnWe'll arrest those miscreants right away.nnIf they run, they won't be allowed back into Ebonheart.
I hear that Ulvil the Ashbane sleeps in the dust. Is that true?
Wild saltrice grows along the banks of the river.nnGather what you can find. Take it to Ashlanders in the shrine.nnI'm sure they're hungry.
<The Daedra glowers at you with barely contained fury.>

Daedra will keep coming out of that portal. To seal it, someone has to dispel the binding placed on it. There must be a clue about that ritual in the ruins below.nnAm I repeating myself? I suppose it doesn't matter.
We came here to find peace. nnWe came to form a community where anyone afflicted with this curse would be safe.nnI just hope Kerbol's Mill will be safe again someday.
As rough as it was, I think you and Agnes may have solved our problem.
All we can offer these soldiers is a choice between life as a werewolf and the risk of the plague. nnI wish we could offer them more.
Did you just... touch me? Who is your owner? nnClearly, you need more beatings.
This affliction has been such a great bother. nnSo many of our guards have died, yet the slaves escaped.nnThese things happen. All will be right in the end.
You've come from Hallin's Stand?nnHaven't seen many travelers from there lately.
Fire salt dust on you and you're in one piece? Both brave and lucky, my friend.
If they see you talking to me, I'll be beaten! nnMaybe you will too!
Get the key off his body. That's all he's good for now. And don't worry, he won't remember a thing when he wakes. If he wakes.
You are leading my egg-brothers to freedom? nnThat is very kind... but I don't think you can protect more than three of us at a time.
Perhaps fate has brought you to me.nnI could use your help preparing the fallen for their journey into the afterlife.
When you're ready to start the ritual, scatter the dust on the gravesites we've prepared.
The Dres manor is on the east side of town. nnWe can't get in there. They've got guards with armor and swords. nnRags and rocks aren't much use against them.
If you can help liberate the city, we'll all be in your debt.nnGods be with you, my friend.
Well met friend. It's good to see some new blood around here. The Fighters Guild is spread pretty thin in Stormhaven. We have our work cut out for us.
I hope you had no problems finding <<1>>.nnNecromancy is always an interesting study, particularly because of the forbidden views many hold, nnVivec's Antlers also presents many amazing opportunity.
Please hurry. I'm not sure how much longer I can keep them from drawing their weapons. nnThere must be a way to break this curse.
Whatever it is you want, I probably can't help you.
I knew she'd be fine without me for a few weeks.
I've heard of you!nnIt's good to see you helping out in Karthdar. I'm here to help you any way I can.nnWhat do you need?
Travel to the southwest. Use the dark tome at the altar there.nnI'll stop the prince from entering Gil Var Delle until you return.
Hmph. Just when I thought we already had enough scum in this town.
These are my private chambers. nnPerhaps the House Father could help you?
What brings you to Kragenmoor?nn We've hard times and dangerous people, but not much else.
A "3"? Middle of the road. nnDo you want to push your luck? You go over six, and it's the end of you.
Use that scroll on a dreaming cultist. Bind him to your will and lead him back here!nnQuickly now! I can't contain this thing much longer.
A bowl of kwama eggs, a slice of scuttle, and horsemeat stew....

I don't care how much my great-grandfather has suffered for his sins.nnWithout that writ, there's no way to prove justice was done or redeem our family's honor.nnChoose me, and I'll help you reclaim Bangkorai Garrison from the Imperials.
We've been lucky here. The only sick we have are the ones who arrived sick.
What do you think? Will Mount Heimlyn erupt?nnI have a brother serving at Heimlyn Keep. He's wagered five gold it won't erupt before he transfers back.nnHe's clever that way.
I appreciate Ufa's intentions.nnI only wish his warning came sooner  much sooner.
Once again, we're in your debt.nnWithout your quick action, <<1>> and her son would both be dead.
Were you just giving me a look? Hmm? Maybe you need a quick search....nnI bet we'd find some skooma on you. You'd have your neck stretched for that, you know.nnI've got some rope. You watch yourself.
Without your help, the Imperials would still have that sword.nnNow they'll never know what happened to it.
During a legendary alit hunt, Patriarch Leyden cast a spell into the face of House Father Sadavel.nnFortunately, the house father apologized for interfering with the patriarch's aim.
Even the inferior may be blessed by the Three. nnRemember the saga of Saint Felms! Though modest of mind, he was mighty, and he drove the heretics from our borders.
It's only a matter of time, I guess.
So another great hero has risen to fight the Imperials.nnThis gives me hope.
Dreughside's returning to normal. We'll cordon off the dreugh and let the guards sort things out.nnGuess your work here's done.
Call on me when you're ready to fight the Imperials at Bangkorai Garrison. nnI won't forget my commitment to you.
Your innocence has been proven. You may leave at any time.
The affliction must be caused by a sinful relic of the dwarves. Use my <<1>> at three pools within these ruins. It will turn blue if the water is pure, and red if contaminated.
What's the matter?nnYou're not afraid of little old me, are you?
With the prisoners freed... at least I'll know that they'll be safe now. But you have to stop Calypsi... or even more of our people will be enslaved!
Tyl sent me to find you here. nnDo you have one of their spellbooks? nnI can help interpret it.
Please work with the captains to stop the riots. nnShutting down the docks is hurting all of Sentinel.
Now that you've had a taste, perhaps you would enjoy another excursion into history.nnMy company and I will soon set out for Ancestor's Landing.nnWe could certainly use another pair of hands.
Go on. Bring me proof that goods are being taxed. nnDon't bother coming back with more promises.nnI want something solid. Something I can sink my teeth into!

Retrieve evidence disproving the rumors. nnI think the Withered Hand's ruffians are somehow responsible for the rumors.nnAnything that repulsive is probably embroiled in some form of treachery. Wouldn't you agree?
What's this? It's the magician!nnI bet you're here to show me I was seeing things. nnConjure something for me, illusionist!
Though she does not want these johads, Jahi has always been a better administrator than our father ever was. It will be an honor to learn from her.
Thank you for rescuing Bahir.nnThe king turned many of my guards into soldiers to support the Daggerfall Covenant.nnNow brave individuals like you are being called upon more often.
From these ruins, a horde of skeletons issued forth.nnWe must put the dead back to rest.
If the Withered Hand is planning something else, I hope we discover what it is quickly. Preferably before they are able to carry it out.
I regret that my father did not heed the warnings of the Ash'abah before, but I am truly grateful that you are here to help set matters straight.nnSometimes one person can make all the difference.
I hope he's alright. Garis has been under a lot of stress lately.
Isn't it pleasant up here? It's far above the dust of the streets, the air is cooler . Between you and me, I think that's why mages build towers. Smart, huh?
Sometimes we can catch fish in the canyon bottom. Not very often, though.
The food we can grow here is so bland. Sometimes I put random things in the stew, just to see if it tastes different.nnTake my advice: avoid slugs.
Ah, fermented bittergreens. Tastes terrible, doesn't get you drunk.nnIf you spin around a few times you can pretend, though.

You were able to recover some of my wares? Thank Almalexia!nnPass the food out to the villagers around the chasm. I've seen what they eat - all mushrooms and bittergreens. I'll turn a profit from this yet!
Go now and light the final brazier. nnDo not fear the power of Tu'whacca. You and I, we are his champions in this.
This Prophet has turned brother against brother. His poison pollutes our nest like rotten flesh. Tell me you have ended his life.
You are the Nest-Mother's chosen? I smell old blood and many traveled miles. Her judgment shall not lead us astray.nnThe one who drives brother against brother will soon be rooted out.
She is dead. She was my friend, and now she is dead. Why did you choose her? Why not me?
Words fail me. Wit dies in throat. Nothing good can be said of this.
This is indeed unfortunate. Rather it were you, lying dead on the sands. <<1>>.
I can't believe they killed her....
May the Three preserve us!
We're better off without a mer-eating monster at the bottom of the canyon. Doesn't really matter whether it was animal or Daedra
I know what you're going to say, child.nnMy apologies, that was not meant as a jest. Go on. Speak of what you've seen.
Your sacrifice is accepted. You may travel these lands freely.
What is your dream? You want to be stronger? Smarter? Faster? nnFor the right price, Unishi will make your dreams come true!
What were you able to find out?
<<1>> was a good man. Whoever is behind these assassinations will hopefully suffer greatly before they meet their just end.
You're the tribe's only hope, <<1>>.nnPlease, keep my husband at my side.

I need poison sacs and goat flesh so I can complete the alchemical mixture. The sacs can be found on scorpions near the camp. Most of the tribe's goats already lie dead.nnHurry, <<1>>. The Ash'abah are depending on you now.
The Nagas must have those barrels of pitch by now. We must strike before they can move against us.
<Marimah is dead.>
The merchant Kilban has been among us for many seasons. If the seeds of Bogmother truly exist, he would be the one to hold them.nnWith that, Bogmother will purge herself of these parasites.
True honor need not be named, my friend, but I'll sure as Oblivion remember your heroics.
Did you speak with <<1>>? We've been preparing for the worst, and, thanks to <<2>>, I think we have the perfect plan to launch an attack.
<<1>> is not the right leader for the Cult of the Fang. He is far too inflexible. Should you choose to challenge him, you have my support.
If we want our movement to be taken seriously, we need more members.  We can't accomplish our goals if we don't have the manpower.
I see a lot of new faces around here thanks to you.  There's an excitement in the air that we haven't had before.
Thanks to you, we have the equipment necessary to operate for the next few weeks.
Lead me away from this place, brave soldier. Take me to safety, please!
Are you really going to just leave her there?
You chose wisely, <<1>>. Now finish your job, and get us safely out of this place.
You can find <<1>> around the nearby huts.
Murkvale was such a pleasant place before all of this happened.

I cannot tell you how relieved I am to hear that the Ansei Ward is safe. I will summon other Ash'abah to come here and help clean out the rest of these Ra-Netu.nnYouyou must go after the third Ansei Ward.
I lead the Cult of the Fang now, <<1>>. You are no longer welcome here.
Go on now. The blade is restored and I must rest. Take it to someone you trust to keep it safe.
...Get to the large house southeast of here. I will distract the captain long enough for her to forget about you.nnAnd keep your head down, lest another guard take too much interest in you....
The way is open to you and your Redguard friend. Once inside, you may not want to leave.nnI welcome you. You may stay as long as you desire. Longer, even.
You have heard my stories. I have no more for you today.nnNow you must learn from the other masters. <<1>> awaits you at the dueling arena.

I hope I can keep up with the orders. Several of the traders are going to work with me on making the meals and running this place.nnThings might actually look up around here for once. Been too long since we could say that.
He lives! nnHa! Of course he lives. He could dance on Sep's flicking tongue, that one. I had no need to worry.
The pirates have no business near the Hist. Show them that this is not their place.
Exiled! My torment shall be without end. I know Raifa considers this merciful, but it is not.nnI do not blame you, either. Not now, at any rate.
The land has begun the process of renewal, with new greenery sprouting up all over the vale. Let this be the legacy of our research; a promise of rebirth for any place, no matter how scarred.
I am concerned about the number of swamp-addled hatchlings in the marsh.nnThis is an Argonian problem, not a <<1>> problem. If you're not interested in helping, please leave me to my business.
I still can't quite believe what's happened. I'm not sure how I will explain it to the younger students.nnNo matter. Leki's Blade needs a strong leader. This duty falls to me.
Such bad, bad dishes. I don't see why they can't behave for a moment. I clean them and dry them and stack them neatly. What more could a dish possibly want?
You have made this day a warm rock, <<1>>. Few pay much attention to <<2>>.nnPlease hurry back before the eggs begin to move.
These Nagas are nothing but bark-gnawers.
Have you listened to the patter of the grasses against your ankles? They say more than you'd think.

Ah, good. Still alive. You are still alive, yes? Strange days. Can't be too sure.nnI asked you to do something, didn't I? Sorry. I've been so wrapped up in this, I forgot what it was. Can't leave this for a moment. Not a moment.
And so it comes to an end, with all of us gathered together at the last.nnThe student. The disciples. The master. And an arbiter!
Teeus will not have died in vain. I will see that many follow him to the soil.
Go speak with <<1>>. He's right in the center of camp.

I've been reading the signals for weeks now. I translated their stories, but the patterns have started... changing. I can't follow them anymore. They've started lying to me. Like they lied to everyone else.
Were you able to discover anything?
Justice sometimes wears a mask. Kindness, revenge, duty. Fate.nnWhat mask did my choice wear this day? Only time will tell.
You really did it. You must be insane!
You've spoken with Nanilvar. I can sense his lingering anger clinging to you like dew on a frond.

You have been very thorough, friend,  and the Withered Hand will not soon forget this day.nnAlas there is more I must ask of you. The town of Satakalaam is under attack and in grave danger. Will you help them?
If you use the amulet to turn the <<1>> against <<2>>, defeating her will be easier.
I wasn't sure about bringing in the prisoners and merchants. But if you trust them, then so will I.
The new recruits were very impressed by you.
I still don't know why the Worm Cult is paying these pirates to raid the river.nnUnless it's to create more corpses. They've certainly been doing that.
You don't have any business with me, outsider.
Looks like the Maormer bit off more than they could chew. Hah!
I will remain here for a while, and urge any others in hiding to travel to Velyn Harbor. Thank you, <<1>>. You've done a fine thing here.
Halt, you scum! Wait you're not one of the Withered Hand. You should be more careful - I nearly killed you.

The Tear of Andrial is what my people called it. A symbol of the pact made between my allies and the forest itself.nnForged by the magic of Valenwood, it was a means to appease the forest. To allow us safe travel when we first arrived.
Long swim.nnPirates everywhere.nnSitting under an old man's tail.nnOnly thrown up twice.nnI think my Khajiit friends would call this a good day.nnHow was your trip?
Have you found the book yet, my ally in love? The merchants in town should have something suitable.
So you come bearing a bracelet of...solid make. I assume the man of deeds has earned your recommendation?
Have you acquired the bracelet yet? One should be available from one of these grubby Crown merchants.
Me? I'm Vexa, a runner for the Jaqspurs... among other things. Right now I'm waiting for a food delivery so's I can get it up to Silvenar.
Don't bother me until you have everything required for the elixir.
Do you need <<1>> to explain where to find the reagents to poison <<2>>?
If the Magistrate was somehow involved in this, she must be brought to justice!
Take a torch and burn those nests. Then tell Pale Talon we won't tolerate another attack.nnHopefully, that will be enough to convince her.
Have you tried these rocks yet?
We are looking for large gazebo structures with orbs inside. Disrupting the orbs is our goal here.

The dead boar is wearing a decorative collar. Faded symbols adorn the fur. Its throat is slit, and a bowl beneath it is encrusted with dried blood.nnThe blood must be one of the ingredients, and the bowl may be used to collect it.
You seek the Harpy Queen? The Harpy Queen is who you seek? Yes? Hmm?

The ogres have paid in blood for what they did. I owe them more death and blood but another debt must be paid, first.nnNo one would have escaped Aswala and the ogres if it were not for the Lion Guard. I owe my life, and my sister's life, to them.
We will always be grateful to you for aiding us, <<1>>. You have done the poor here a great favor with your help.
It is always a pleasure to do business with you, <<1>>. How are you this beautiful day?
Let me know when you have the crown. It is of vital importance that you bring it to me as soon as you can!

A blessing on your family for your actions, friend. Old Split Thumb is no more, thanks to you.nnNow that the ogre's defeat is assured my heart turns to our lost horses that wander the desert. Will you aid me again by seeking them out?
The Tear... it can still save many, just like it saved us so long ago.
This is the first fight I've been in for two decades. My hands are shaking like a hatchling's.nnEh. Probably just arthritis. Are we going to be here much longer?
You think the pirates will be frightened if I claim to be a vomitomancer?

Inila never trusted me, but she was a crafty one. If she had evidence against Munada, she would hide it. Her apartment is above the bookseller by the tavern. I did not have time to search it.nnSearch her room for what we both seek: justice!

All I wanted out of life was to protect something. The future. A town. A person. A vault. I thought, "There seem to be guards everywhere. There's a future in it."nnI have no idea what I'm guarding out here. Necromancers?

Elennae told me how you helped her. Now the necromancer is cut off from the power of the ruins, but I still do not know where he hides.nnMy other assistant, Meliara, was searching to the north for something to assist in that.
A weight has been lifted from the town. I can feel it in the air and in the streets. nnHave you destroyed the auras?
While Meliara digs up rocks for some unknown purpose, you and I will be able to get something useful accomplished. I greatly appreciate your assistance in this while I am... inconvenienced by injury.
I've reached an impasse with <<1>> and <<2>>, the other two leaders of our expedition. If we can't come to an accord, I fear what <<3>> might do.
The nightshade grows in the shelter of greater trees around the shrine. They are not native, but have taken root here nonetheless.nnI will prepare for the ritual. We must be swift.
Ah, <<1>>. You've aquired a disguise. Good. It's quite becoming on you.
I'd board that pirate ship myself to see what they bring the cult. But if I did, it might cause... an ill wind between the Worm Cult and my caste.

Joile's betrayal taught us yet another virtue: cautionwariness. We remain slow to trust, but loyal beyond measure. nnYou have reached the summit! The Make-Way God, sees much at this height. Have you learned the greatest lesson of this place?
I wish I could believe harpy attacks are a thing of the past!
You should play again! Yes, yes! M'adric thinks this is wise.nnDo you think you are good enough to win once more?
Thank you for your help, stranger. I couldn't bear the burden of my past another step.
The best theft is the kind that Bosmer law lets me get away with! Thanks again, <<1>>.
I received reports of combat taking place just beyond the village walls. I assume that was you?
I sense their corruption upon you. Use this against them. Find out the purpose of this "blessing," and from that their motives will be divined.
The Mayor might know where my friend is. If anyone knows, you'd think he would.
You lied to me! You said you'd let me take the credit. What kind of unscrupulous <<1>> are you, to do such a thing!  You've ruined me!
What is with all these cats? Makes no sense.nnAnyways, something around here... it has the smell. Check around.
They are wasting my time. I should steal a horse and flee this fly-infested pit. nnI have too much respect for their people to break all the eggs before I leave.
I can't believe they're letting me TOUCH the eggs. This is a breakthrough for my research.
The past is an impossible burden. Why should one be forced to carry it?
Go on. I will not suffer the humliation of being arrested. I will turn myself in.
I did not see you in this garden before, wayfayer. Be welcome!nnI await my beloved. Roses are her favorite. Their scent reminds me of her .
Help <<1>> find out what's become of Casnar.nnPlease hurry! If we don't find Casnar soon, I fear there will be bloodshed.
The river pirates must not damage our eggs! Speak to <<1>>. He will know how best you can help.
There you are - just as the Prophet predicted! He was waiting for you, with the Nord woman Titanborn. He told me you would come.
<<1>>, the necromancers are bristling with uneasiness. Have they found something of import, or have you?
Without the conduits, the Champion's tomb is sealed. He alone holds the key to the inner sanctum, the resting place for the Skull of Yotunmir.

I am very grateful to you for helping me to put out the fires. I did not expect that to happen!nnI haven't figured out a new plan for how to stave off the Imperial Army, yet, but I'm working on it. I'm sure I'll come up with something!

Not surprisingly, the Mages Guild of Wayrest is in the Mages District. nnFor a small fee, they'll send you to the Mages Guild in Shornhelm. That's in Rivenspire.nnOnce you arrive, find the local Ancestor Moth chapterhouse. Talk to the priests.
You better have a good reason for bothering me. Running this village takes a lot of time.

The shield is restored for now. This should buy us a little more time anyways.nnThe Imperials will need to be dealt with from the outside. All we can do is keep hidden and hope for the best of resolutions.
What were those loud fiery noises coming from outside?nnWait... I don't want to know.
Blinded by hope, the vision came too clearly. The <<1>>, broken! I should have seen better.nnHow to repair this? I must consult the scrolls. The scrolls, Lyris! We must go. I must see again.
It is vitally important that no intruders can wield Oblivion-fire in Malabal Tor, regardless of their intent. The tome must be destroyed!
Wait, is it really you? How did you... what are you doing here? Did you run across the scout I sent into the Imperial camp?
Help us bring Rama to justice. He's responsible for this slaughter.
You'll find this girl in the tree home right above the Thane's home. He has given these Risen refugee there for now.nnGo speak to her. Find out why this has to be stopped.
You have served the Dominion well, <<1>>. Continue your fine work.
We must find the Imperial supply caches and set fire to them before we can proceed with the next step of the mission.
There is something different about you, <<1>>. Something familiar. nnAre you wearing my clothes? You shouldn't borrow your king's clothes without permission, you know.
You're both crazy. Killing Master Muzguthere must be another way!
Please. Show mercy. You can't leave me here with these savages.
The dreugh attacked in the night, but we got some of them! The boys are ripping apart their bodies. nnIf we catch any more, we're cooking them alive. They'll pay for this!
Stay away unless you've got real business for me.nnI'd be glad to have one of my boys air out the inside of your neck.
You've been gone some time. Have you collected the eyes?
I wish there was another way, but if this allows me to rejoin my brother, so be it.
<<1>>, the necromancers are bristling with uneasiness. Have they found something of import, or have you?
You have seen through the veil that clouded your vision. Rajeren thinks you see clearly, now, but are the clouds gone?nnFace your deciever, <<1>>. Test your resolve. Rajeren cannot help you in this.
My clan said I would come to a bad end. This is about the worst end of Black Marsh.
Until <<1>> found the golden skull, the trade coteries found more prestige in their raiding rituals. Now all they care for is the right to hold the skull.
So? Have you found enough zombie heads to build a lodge?nnI've told the rest of the coterie. We're all eager to see this.
The Ayleids are among us.nnSpeak with them. I will observe.

Speak to the members of our coterie. When you have learned of our ways, tell <<1>> how you would divide the goods taken from the Kothringi village. She stands at the crossroads to the northwest, just outside our storage pen.
Your repair of the totem could show you possess the beginnings of wisdom. nnIt could also show you simply have a meddlesome nature.nnTime will tell, I suppose.
The towers. Were you able to close the conjuration boxes in the towers?
Making a keen edge is harder than it looks. You have to hit the rock just... so....
My allies have already begun, <<1>>, but your help will be extremely useful.
Your prowess is impressive, <<1>>. Perhaps you could help us clean up here?
Unbeliever! You walk the path to righteousness, and it was I who showed you the way.nnMaruhk, forgive me!
If what you say about the Dream Shard is true, Adima must be allied with the Supernal Dreamers.nnThat makes poor Hosni nothing but a pawn in all this.
Well if it isn't gro-Izburg errand boy.
Where's the sword? What happened?
I hear there's been real trouble over in Camlorn. Something about werewolves.

Well met, traveler. The Aldmeri Dominion and the Ebonheart Pact are marching on the Imperial City. We are mobilized, but our supply lines are stretched dangerously thin.nnWill you restore the balance and aid the war effort?
One day, when I'm not wounded, I hope we can fight side by side.nnPerhaps that day, we can chase these deceitful Daedra away together!

<<1>> lives in the house just north of the inn. For now, I just need you to go there and make sure she's not about to engage in any more rash behavior. nnI'll get my men and meet you there shortly to take her into custody.
These Daedra will soon falter without the will of their leader. You have earned our friendship well.

The villagers may not realize it, but you saved this town from crumbling into chaos.nnI mentioned before that I came from Alcaire Castle. The situation there is critical, and I think you might be able to make a difference.
Were you able to speak to <<1>>?nnI haven't attempted to contact my brother yet. The guards advised against it.
So Dame Dabienne wasn't working with the slavers after all.nnThat's a relief.

I've been constable here at Koeglin Village for more than a decade. I haven't let the town down so far, and I don't mean to do so today.nnThat ship is a threat. I'll see it gone even if I have to sink it myself.

In all my years sailing these seas, I have never received such ill treatment in a friendly port. nnMy men lie here bleeding on deck, and we are refused aid.nnThis man they call constable is a son of a dog  or did he change his mind?
I just can't believe my Rosalie would  it's just unthinkable.nnI owe you for my life, and for my daughter's welfare. Though she wants to thank you herself.

If Constable Pascal sent you here with orders to open the forge, you can just turn around and head right back out the door.nnThat man has no right to order me around, and I'm not about to issue weapons for his witch hunt.
My poor little baby  all alone out there .nnIf you're leaving the village, if you could please look out for my son. With these slavers about, I'm afraid something terrible has happened.
Please. Please hurry! I have a feeling something terrible is going to happen! nnShe wouldn't hurt my father, would she?
I don't understand what happened to the general, but I will say he just hasn't been himself lately.nnIf there's anything I can do to help him, please let me know.
Don't let them eat my Ganny. Save my girl, please!
You've done so much for us already, but I still have something to ask of you, if I may.
There are Ayleid ruins all along the pass. The fragments we need should be inside them.nnThe bloodfiends and their thralls collect Varla Stones. They might not part with them easily.
You're so brave. I hope there's someone who cares about you, somewhere.
You defeated the champions? Quickly, talk to Count Hosni!nnNow we'll see if he's true to his word.
We must consider how best to take advantage of your capacity for mayhem. nnWhat do you think, my dear? More theatrics? A helm with bigger horns?

I hadn't expected to see you again so soon.nnNo doubt Verandis would be interested in speaking to you. Of course, I have more pressing matters to attend to. Our enemies grow stronger with each passing moment.
Well, I guess you're Hammerdeath Arena's new champion.nnJust goes to show, you shouldn't judge by appearances.
A challenge? I hate to ask, but please say you'll take it.
Hurry! Make the potion.nnDo not fear the power of the ancients, friend.
We'll have to cut a path through our enemies to reach the White-Gold Tower. Get ready to shed some blood!
<<1>>! The bearer of the staff returns. Has your burden been borne? Did the foundation to the Nirnpith restore our charge?
Thanks to you, the foals have been returned.nnMy brothers spirits' have been gone a long time. I hope they can find their way back to their bodies.

You have the blood of Suturah's heirs. This tainted lifeforce will shatter the enchantment protecting the necropolis vault.nnYou'll find <<1>> sealed within it. Reclaim the Ansei Ward and stop the ritual. Save Alik'r!
Back so soon. Good. Learn anything?
Do you have anything to report?
Help Wyress Jehanne, please.
We're ready for the nobles. You're giving them a signal, right?
My sisters and I should be able to open a path to safety, but we'll need your help again to make this work.
My father and I were both deeply saddened to hear of my sister's death. nnI understand you made the call to execute her murderer. You made the right choice, and I thank you for it.
I should have never left her. I ... I don't know what I'll do from here.nnHer face ... I'll never forget her face.
I'm sure Faolchu would call mercy a weakness. But I think it shows strength of character. nnWe're going to need such strength in the days ahead.
You can find Sibellec in the northern Wyrd camp. Just follow the road across the bridges.
You'll find Sarvith in the tent behind me. nnAnd please remind Sarvith to be careful. He's brilliant, but he doesn't always pay as much attention to detail as he should.

What are we still standing around for? Let's go find the Daggers and get this job done.nnWith the gold that Lord Diel pays us, we can set up a shop within the city and buy proper uniforms and everything.
Search the house. As <<1>> says. If you find nothing, I must assume Ohama's lying and throw her and my fool brother out.nnThat is, if he ever shows up again, the lazy slug.
My brother and I will pack up here and follow behind you.nnAny harpies you catch in the throwing snare, we'll be sure to haul in and get back to camp.
Well! I didn't think she'd kill him. That wasn't what I planned.nnStill, he got what he deserved.
You have returned. And you are victorious. Just as I have foreseen it.

Those soldiers tried to kill <<1>>, but she got them first. She said she was going to hide in a house north of the temple until she could strike back. nnI can't let her risk herself like that. What am I to do?
Thanks to you, Aswala Stables has been saved!nnWe won't forget what you've done for us.
Please finish this. Retrieve the sword from the chapel and take it to the burial vault where Rosalind died.nnDo what I cannot and face my poor wife's shade.
We're safe for the moment, Captain. Go find your husband.
Dresan Keep you said . Why does that sound familiar to me?

Fried fire salts! This is way worse than I realized. nnThe Withered Hand, eh? When I get back to the tower, I'll see if I have anything on them  it'll be useful when you come ask for my help again, which I'm sure you will.
I pray that we are not too late to stop the Withered Hand, and with the same breath, I thank the gods for guiding you here.nnTu'whacca watch over you, wayfarer.
Good to see you again. We owe you a great deal, you know.
Well done. When we get back to town, I'll raise a tankard in your name.

Thanks to you, the source of the Daedric threat is gone. When my sword arm recovers, I'll join the hunt for those Withered Hand scum. I will not rest until the sands of Alik'r are stained with their blood!nnGo with Onsi's blessing, <<1>>.
I've heard a lot of greetings, but that one's new to me.
I'm afraid there isn't much time. nnWe expect Faolchu to launch a full-scale assault at any moment.
You're back! Tell me, what did you see?
I think one of those spiders bit me. I feel a little woozy.nn<<1>>  sounds familiar but I can't put my finger on it.
Meet us at the ritual site. And don't forget the lurcher.
It is well, but there is more to do. We cannot rest just yet.
You did it. You killed Faolchu.

I have realized what I must do. nnI will build a shrine to honor my fellow priests that were slain here  it will be an everlasting testament to their sacrifice and to the temple's ability to persevere.
Wonderful! We'll slip past their very noses. Just like in the stories!
Risking danger just to recover trinkets for me. Our family will always remember this.
We are in your debt, friend. I hope you made Angof suffer before you finished him!
You made it. No zombie bites or anything.
Camlorn is free! It may take a while, but we're going to recover from Faolchu's vile touch.
These cursed werewolves. I just . nnHow in Oblivion did you get in here?
Thank you for directing the women here. They will be well cared for.
Sanded maple. Open your journal. Recipe is inside.
Father's at peace now. I need a change of scenery, so I'm going to Stormhaven.nnMaybe I'll see you there one of these days.
You and Tamien handle whatever's going on in the house. I'll play lookout and make sure no one sneaks up on you.
If you truly offer your assistance, I welcome it readily. Our numbers are weakened by the poison used against my people.nnI'm not sure how much longer we can keep the undead at bay.
Please. Go away! There is  nothing you can say that willl console me.nnMy sweet Casnar is either dead, or he's decided he doesn't love me!  I-I don't know which is worse!
Must be nice. Being able to just walk out of here and do whatever you want.
We'll need all the armor and weapons you can find. nnJust think how grateful some of these sweet young citizens will be.
Activate the stones in the four huts. My sisters need a safe place to work.

The workers owe you their lives. I pray you're not too late to rescue the dockmaster. nnBahir may be old, but he's got a spark to him. If these risen dead weren't of our people, I've no doubt he could hold his own.
So far, it's been rough trying to get anyone to listen. I hope you're having better luck than me.
We established a perimeter around the village. Nothing that comes this way will get past us.nnBut we can't cover the docks. I don't have enough soldiers for that.
Unfamiliar with Sentinel?nnThe inn is just east of here. The smithy is on the far east side. The alchemist is in the market, just south of the inn.
The cure won't work unless the werewolves are weakened first. nnRemember. Weaken them, then use the antidote. Send anyone who's cured back here.

You're going to help us, eh?nnI could have figured this out, you know. If I could find a way to weigh the harpy down so it'd trigger the trap  you know what? It's probably better that you take care of this.
Very few outside of the royal family have been inside that crypt, <<1>>. You should feel honored that <<2>> chose you for this task.nnDo you have the amulet?
Collect the keys and bring Anton's jeweled crown to me. I'll reward you handsomely. nnEven better, I'll mention you in my next book.
Friend, I am blessed that you came along.nnIf you could discover the young soldier's fate, I would be in your debt.
I overheard what the archmagister said. You need someone from Padesh's family as a sacrifice.nnI'm ready.
Have you chosen your sacrifice?nnIs it <<1>> or <<2>>?
You took back my city.nnWe will rebuild and Camlorn will rise again. Thank you for everything you've done.
Ha! Now you're just showing off. nnBut I'm glad to see you alive and well. Darien, too. Tamriel would be a poorer place without the two of you in it.
I have failed everyone!
This plan sounds crazy, but I wish you both luck.nnGuard Scholar Dariya with your life.
I tried to stop him, but it was all I could do just to keep him from killing Father Quiston!nnDamn it all! What are we going to do now?
Now comes the time to prove yourself, <<1>>.nnYour strength and wisdom is needed elsewhere in Alik'r.
<<1>> must be stopped. What he is doing is a crime against the Divines!
I cannot help you against the Imperials until the souls of my retainers are safe.nnPlease find them soon.
I think perhaps I had our assignments wrong. I should've checked the stocks and sent you to check the ship.
Thank you for dealing with this small matter for me.nnI'm afraid <<1>> has me overtasked at the moment.

The wells are in the Imperial camp north of us. <<1>> is usually in the northeast part of the camp. Good riddance to him.nn<<2>>  I don't know how to say this, but you're the first person I've ever trusted. Thank you for helping me.
Come now, I don't expect that switch is just going to throw itself. nnIf you'll get the switch, I'll go on into the chamber. Then you can just meet me inside.
